text:
If u like crawling little bugs, layers upon layers of paint covering up dirt, filthy carpet, dingy breakfast port hole, and holes in the fabric of chairs and curtains, then you've found your place! 
The staff is super nice, when you check out, they surprise you with "I have just one charge for you, $10 for parking." All said with a smile, of course. 
Definitely a place I'll remember. 
I would suggest getting drunk next door bef you check in.

Geno's is definitely a Philadelphia icon but the steaks really are just average. They seem to be giving less steak in their sandwiches over the years as well but maybe its just in my head :P 

If you have a friend visiting from out of town take them there! But as your everyday cheese steak I'd visit your local pizza shop

I would give it zero stars but I couldn't. The staff is so clueless.  Not sure if they know they are at Pizza Hut.  Regardless, after a long day at the parks I decided to order a "quick" pizza.  Yeah, that wasn't the case.  I'm glad I do not live here and I was just visiting.  I do not recommend this place.  By the way, I'm still waiting on my pizza as I write this...

Look at that, they didn't even have an order for me.  After an hour, I gave up.  I highly recommend going somewhere elder.

Mirnas is decent most of the time - we live nearby and when we don't feel like cooking after work, we may go here.  Pasta is ok, Mediterranean dishes best, chicken sometimes good, sometimes not.  Servers are efficient, they never ask if you want something to drink so odd.

We had dijnner there on Saturday night.  There were 9 of us and there was something wrong with everyone's dinner.  Two prime ribs came out luke warm (tell you later about that), two pasta dishes came with the wrong noodle (asked the waitress and she told us we were wrong - it was the right noodle and it wasn't- she then told us that they ran out of angel hair pasta, pasta with chicken parm was not hot, macaroni and cheese for my grandson was bland and no taste - he didn't eat it, chicken marsala lacking something, and my dish was okay not alot of vegetables for a vegetarian dish.
We called over the manager who was the general manager and he told us that prime rib is served at room temperature.  He was not at all sorry and did nothing to make us happy.  The water, coffee, etc. never got refilled unless we flagged down the waitress.
She was not at all nice or helpful.  One prime rib was sent back and it came out 2 minutes later - the same piece only it was microwaved (we were told that) and the other prime rib was sent back with instructions not to microwave and send out a new piece.  By the time it came, we were all done.  We decided not to order dessert even though we were celebrating 2 birthdays that evening.  When we got the check nothing was taken off for all the problems but the 15% was automatically added on for the waitress.  The manager was not at all apologic and lacked management skills.  None of the party plan to return to this restaurant.

I picked this florist after reading other reviews on Yelp, and was still pleasantly surprised. I had called a different place first, and the communication barrier was so bad that I couldn't even place an order. I called Yosi's because my parents are traveling through Tucson on my mom's birthday, and I wanted to send her flowers to their hotel. I called in the mid-afternoon on the day I wanted them delivered. They were friendly, helpful, listened to what I wanted, and offered me various price ranges. They delivered the flowers to her hotel just a few hours later! Would definitely recommend to anyone.
I came by Datz the other night to grab a couple drinks at the bar! Its a great place to relax and get a good bite to eat! Hannah at the bar was awesome and made the best drinks! Check this place out!

Out of all your choices at Comcast center, Percy Street gives you something delicious and different. I don't eat BBQ that often for lunch, especially in Philadelphia where hoagies are king.

The menu is simple, you have either sandwich or platter of pulled pork, brisket, or chicken. I like that; not complicated and stick to what is good. Sides range from cole slaw, beans, mac-n-cheese, cornbread, collards. I ordered the brisket platter which comes with cole slaw, either beans or collards, and a slice of cornbread. It was a healthy platter, when I like something I can put it down but I was full by the end. With a drink, my total was $11 which isn't too shabby for Comcast dining. 

The only con I see is that they do not give you enough BBQ sauce. It was about half of a shot class which didn't cover all my brisket. I ended up mixing a lot of my platter together so I was fine, but would like more sauce.

I started off having a horrible time at this Casino. My room was the wrong and my sheets had hair in them. After I got that squared away, later in the night security was totally rude about me sitting at the sports betting "yes we were betting". I was more than 10' from anyone while having a drink kicked my wife and myself out for not having a mask on. Thanks Peppermill for the shit night..

We are totally finished with this place. We gave it another chance because everyone can have a bad day. Three of our party of four actually got sick after we ate there. Just the worse service and food we have ever experienced. Save your money people and go somewhere else.

Kind of remind you of Cheers, where everyone knows your name. It's like being in a neighborhood bar when you're right off the French Quarter. Food wasn't bad, nothing too fancy, but you get the feeling it was more authentic than some of the other places. Stop in for a beer and  a Po boy

The bagels here are pretty good. They are boiled, not steamed, so they have a nice crust on the outside and soft on the inside. The cream cheese is delicious, and their eggs are made on the flat top right in front of you. 

However, the building itself is very run down. The outside patio is dingy and dirty. The building is in dire need of a renovation, not from being outdated but from being rundown and not maintained. 

The cashier is an older gentleman that owns the restaurant. I can tell that he spends all of his profits on his Mercedes that is always parked out front, and not on the restaurant building itself. He brags about his Mercedes and how he buys cars for his children. If you pay with a credit card he will try to put your credit card in his pocket to jokingly steal it from you and go shopping. What he doesn't realize is this is not funny, it is rather annoying.

I would have loved to give this restaurant a full five stars. Certainly the food is definitely delicious. However the staff seem very stressed out, and the cashier thinks that he's friendly but he's not. And the establishment itself is very rundown.

I really wanted to give this restaurant five stars because the restaurant is very quaint and I truly enjoyed the owner who waited on us.  But likeability and service just don't make up for the unfortunate fact that the food is simply moderate at best.  Philly, and south Philly especially have some of the most formidable Mexican restaurants around.  I will probably not go back to this place again; in this town, you gotta do a better job with your Mexican.  Sorry guys!

Love the wines but do not care for this tasting room, especially in comparison with others in SB/funk zone.  The staff (constantly changing), is not nice or accommodating...even to wine club members.  The room is extremely loud.  Please do better, Melville.
Love the French toast  they were perfect! The server was so lovely! Thank you so much

Well, I just scanned the many other reviewers for East Beach Wine and sad to say all the sentiments to the owner (David?) is the same: snotty and impolite and arrogant. 

I went years ago to a Spanish wine tasting when they were at Milpas and was unimpressed. Last night went with some friends (they wanted to go in) and forgot it was the same place I went to. 

I asked the owner for a certain bottle, he responded in such a curt, trite manner.

I joined my friends in the up stairs tasting room and felt I was in some granny's attic. I bare light bulb stuck on a wall glaring in your eye, dark wood old chairs and table that look like they were gotten at a garage sale (and not the cool, old antique or shabby chic style) and a hodge podge of things they were selling and a nice sized opening in the wall with a great view of a very messy office.

Needless to say,  I'll never go to East Beach Wine again.

I tried to defend this business but after dealing with them for the last two years, I've had enough. In two years we went through 5 separate community managers. Each one of them were different and had their own way of doing business. In the end we the board asked for a sit down with the owner and instead of meeting with us we were given our walking papers (they resigned). Sad thing is our community had been with them for 23 straight years. Sad the way the new management is running down a once proud company.

On the one hand, it's always nice to see ANY food sometimes when one is traveling at weird hours. Due to a grueling schedule, I needed some late night grub in an unfamiliar city, and they delivered. The nice lady that took my order, also delivered it. On the other hand, it arrived to my hotel room with nary a napkin or utensil in sight.

 It could be the best food in the world, but if one has to eat it with their hands and wipe their mouth with a hotel wash rag, it's gonna cost a couple of stars. Decent eats, friendly service, but remember to ASK for stuff to eat it with if you're getting a delivery!

I was driving through the neighborhood and saw the sign for cajun food so I had to come in. Unfortunately it just let me down. I really wanted cheese fries but they said there is no cheese in house. So I got the crab fries and they were so skimpy, absolutely not worth it. I also ordered the oysters which were okay. I also got some hush puppies which were the best thing I had. This place serves seafood in a steamed plastic bag which isn't my preference. Just really did not enjoy the meal and won't return again. Service was great, though.

This place is a joke. My husband made an appointment last week for our 2 dogs for today. He showed up today and the associate said oh there's only room for one. My husband said no it's for 2 dogs that's why I took this appointment so they could be done at the same time. She literally said, 'well too bad, there's only room for one." My husband cancelled the appointment. You won't get our business again. What a joke. It took a week to get a dual appointment. Terrible customer service.

My husband and I used the private event space to have a belated wedding celebration here in December.  We had a fantastic experience with their event planner, Zack, and his team.  Yards was in transition to their new facility as we were planning the event, and Zack was great with communicating with us along the way.  The venue was beautiful and service was fantastic.  The night before the party, we had a beer and a (yummy) snack at the bar downstairs - when I asked for the same beer upstairs the next night, they didn't have it but they got a pitcher of it for me even though I was happy to try something else, then kept the pitcher refilled all night! The team worked beautifully with our other vendors ensuring our cake, food, dj, and decorations were all in place.  I like to do everything myself so it is done to my standards, and Zack was adamant that I just show up and enjoy myself and they would take care of everything else - he was right! 100% would recommend Yards.

One of my favorite local chains! Cafe patachou is delicious! My favorite breakfast here is: the California dreamer omelette, cinnamon toast, lightly dressed green salad, and drip coffee. I love the breakfast menu so much that I've rarely tried the lunch food, but it certainly looks just as good! I have tried the tomato soup, and it is great, creamy, flavorful!

Over-priced and not worth the wait times for food & drinks. Parking is impossible to find and often will be in a paid lot. I will not be coming back due to consistently poor service and their decision to discriminate patrons by vaccination status. Don't bother commenting that you care about guests safety if your restaurant was open during the pandemic before vaccines were available.

Another reviewer wrote "if you want a mediocre experience come here." That is exactly what I experienced. In fact, I had not read the reviews before I came in, but was completely let down by the experience.
The interior is very nice, that is why it gets two stars. Other than that, this is not worth the money or the time.
I found the sushi to be bland, lukewarm, and totally uninspired. The California Roll was the worst I have ever had... We're talking gas station quality here. The Miso soup was ok, but still very uninspired in its flavor. The salad was good with a sauce I really enjoyed. The best part of the meal was the two pieces of pineapple at the end. 
I see no reason to ever visit here again and do not recommend it.

OK so I've gone to this place a total of three times, once when they were down the street on Gulf Blvd  and now twice at their new location. I find that the breakfast seems to be their strong suit. I have to admit that I ordered bananas Foster over a waffle on two of the three occasions. We were really happy with the service and atmosphere. The food was also quite good. My chai latte came only lukewarm but the barrister came back apologized and prepared another one for me that was steaming hot. I would definitely recommend this place over the two other neighboring places, Beverlys and Jackie's.

So excited that Poke Bros is now in North Wilmington! We have visited a few times since its grand opening and anticipate it will be a regular feature in our takeout rotation. 

They offer several pre-designed poke bowls (BF really likes the Hula, featuring shrimp!), but I like the freedom of designing my own. On my first visit, I designed a bowl with a brown-rice base with salmon and spicy tuna on top, which was delicious but dry, leaving me a bit underwhelmed and disappointed. On subsequent visits, I realized my mistake: leaving out the OG sauce (a soy sauce-like liquid that adds both flavor and moisture) --- I wish the staff would have asked if I wanted to add it the first time because it's a game-changer!

My go-to bowl starts with a mix of sushi rice and brown rice (you can do a 50-50 split of base, options including white rice, brown rice, sushi rice, and mixed greens --- I def recommend at least partial sushi rice for flavor). I then add cucumber, edamame, avocado ($1 extra), masago, crabstick ($1 extra), green onion, with salmon as my main protein (sometimes a 50-50 salmon/tuna mix). I finish with a mix of Sriracha mayo, Coconut Ginger sauce (and, of course, OG sauce), and tempura crunchies. I love that I get to enjoy all the flavors of sushi with significantly less cost (and probably more food). 

They offer a tofu option for the vegetarians among us, and chicken for those who just don't do seafood.

As several reviews have stated, the service is slow at times and they typically have one person follow you through the entirety of the encounter, which may not be the most efficient way to handle things. I also think it might help if the servers suggest toppings so that patrons say yes/no and don't miss any ingredients (I have definitely forgotten to ask for ingredients and been sad when I got home with my bowl!). 

Other FYIs: There is online ordering, though I haven't tried it and can't speak to its success yet. They also offer a loyalty program where they hole-punch a card and offer free bowls after a certain number of punches. Plenty of parking as it is within a shopping center, and usually plenty of seating as many people opt for take-out.
Friendly staff, good food! Boulevard oysters were great & the crab cakes were definitely my fav. Definitely recommend

French Market Inn is conveniently located right on Decatur which gives you easy access to lots of shopping and views of the Mississippi river. The Natchez docks right across the street so you hear the horns and music all through out the day. It was the perfect location for the Halloween parade which goes right past the hotel. Perfect location for that. 

I've stayed here several times over the past two decades. After a really bad experience, I swore that I would never be back... but years passed... and I went back. The affordable price sucked me back in. They remodeled and changed things up quite a bit since my last visit. It really is beautiful. I was impressed. Until I took a closer look. There were red stains ALL OVER THE SHOWER. I called up housekeeping. was it blood? what was it? I think we figured out it was probably Hurricane juice had been splashed around. Did they work on cleaning it? Heck no, so I took pics to show everyone. This was also paying full price during Halloween weekend 2013 for my husband's 50th birthday adventure. Why didn't I learn? But then again, Location, Location Location... the Halloween parade was right outside our door. 

Ugh... and I still am traumatized about the time before this one that I stayed... it was a room up front on the second floor which was above a restaurant that is no longer there now. They came up to my room thinking my bathtub was over running but it wasn't, just stopped up... and it stayed stopped up the whole time I was there, never was fixed, never apology, never a discount... which also meant that we weren't able to clean ourselves. How is that acceptable?  This was before Yelp, many years ago. Same hotel company still owns it.  

On another trip tho, it was more of an anniversary trip in "off season" Dec... we checked in and were upgraded to the King Suite, top floor overlooking the Mississippi River. That was our best stay. Actually, I think the four of five times that I've stayed here, my room always faced the river so I think I've been pretty darn lucky. That's a huge plus if you don't mind the traffic and noise of Decatur. Oh and the music of the Steamboat Natchez throughout the day. A balcony would have made it sooo much sweeter... but the view of the parking lot and river is easy to deal with. Who's hanging in the room anyways. 

Johnny's Po-Boys is right around the corner... famous for their... Po-Boys!!! 

I miss the Voodoo Bar being downstairs. I met the magician actor Harry Anderson (from the TV series Night Court) there once. I pretty sure it's also where I first tasted the local Abita beer, Amber is my favorite.

Their valet takes your car to a garage about a block away. You may go in and out as often as you wish. I don't remember prices off hand, but parking in the quarter expect to pay high dollar no matter what. 

Usually the price is right here. Don't expect anything fancy. 
Don't expect good service. Don't expect much. 
You get what you pay for.

This place was pretty fancy. It was very seems to be a popular hit in town for the locals. I enjoyed my food definitely want to try other places but this one's definitely some place I'd like to visit again
Excellent food and ambiance. Very New Orleans, but with unique twists to some of the dishes. Great, fresh ingredients.

So good!!!! Perfect serving sizes, and great, friendly service!

The spinach lasagna was so good, I'll probably crave it in a couple weeks and have to come back!

I came here because it was recommended by a friend. I have only had pho twice before I came here, once at the Cherry Hill Mall and again at a small pho place on rt 70. I can say this was definitely my best experience with pho so far. The place at the mall almost ruined pho for me as it doesn't seem fresh and they microwave it to heat it up. I'm glad I didn't let that ruin it for me because the pho here seemed completely fresh and was much better tasting. Unfortunately there wasn't a whole lot of vegetarian options but that wasn't a problem at all because it's just as good without meat. The staff was very friendly and  the food came out very quickly. It is cash only so come prepared. There isn't anything bad I can really say about this place it was an overall good experience.

Update.... I did finally use the gift card they sent me. I was unable to place my order online. They don't process gift cards online! Lol! Then the instructions from the online site and the person at the location: fill the online order out, just type in "pay at location". It wouldn't do that. So when I called the girl finally asked me if I wanted to go ahead and place my order, which I did. (This ended up being over $90, and didn't go on the points program... but, they did fix steak without peppercorn, all steaks were listed with that.(yuck! I hate pepper.) We got NY steak -rare (raw), bkd pot, green bns and scallops (4 scallops seemed small and seemed undercooked.) the Lobster Feast Rock lobster, Maine lobster, seafood linguini, bkd pot and green bns.  Only one drawn butter in the little to go container. I think2 of each drawn and regular butter would have been good, all I got for both potatoes was one each whipped little container. The steak was not bleeding, or bloody, it was raw! I swear I heard "moo moo" when I cut into it. But guess I would rather have it undercooked than over. As mentioned, the scallops were not firm, but squishy, the mane lobster tail was also slightly under done. I just heated things up to be sure they were ok. Everything else was really pretty good. Now, was it worth the amount before the gift card? I don't know. 
Also ordered extra biscuits (GREAT!) chocolate cake and apple (blossom) these were supposed to come with ice cream, when I asked if they could put the ice cream in separate containers, I was then told that they didn't have any. Were not having any ice cream because of COVID-19. Really? If it had just been me, I would have cancelled those, I mean, about $13 for this, I think someone could buy some at the store. I was concerned that the girl doing the curbside delivery didn't have a mask on. I am high risk, part of the reason I used curbside... no mask, undercooked food... does this location have their stuff together yet? I hope so. They were very nice this time. Order was correct.

Fantastic pizza and appetizers in a cute niche of town. 
Compared to other local pizza places like Bazbeaux, Napolese definitely blows the other out of the water (out of the oven?)
 Jessie's Pie (seasonally offered) and the Hammaker's Corner are two of my favorite pizzas there. 
Their server is a really cool guy too!

Napolese is my #1 choice for Indianapolis pizza.

Lovely environment. The garlic knots are awesome and the butter is delicious! Ordered lemonade and it wasn't good at all, but the server was efficient and offered to get a new one (with more sugar) but I settled with the water. The pizza is really good, the pepperoni is salami so a tad different than what most are used to. It's good but wasn't the best brick oven pizza we've had. The service was prompt and restaurant was busy and loud (a little past happy hour), but clean and laid back for a magazine spot full of wine.

I tried their all you can eat bbq.  As a korean, I wasn't sure how good their marinated meat would be.  To be brutally honest, the marinated meat was not really korean but more chinese in flavor.  The marinated beef was the closest to being korean but still lacked flavor so I put more of the korean bbq sauce on it before putting it on the grill.  

Other than the marinated meat, other meats were quite good quality.  The ice cream they give when you check in was also really awesome!! Especially the green tea flavor-not too sweet and more matcha flavor.

So, I bought a house last year (yay!). And, then I realized I needed to fill it (boo?). For the majority of my time I work from home (yay!). But sitting on the couch/kitchen table just was not conducive to the space I now had (boo?). Since I am without kids for now, I had a bedroom with big windows, a window seat, wonderful light, and fantastic views to use as an office. I have a fancy printer, briefcase, diplomas, fancy rug, and all other sort of office things. I just needed a big ol' desk and a modern, ergonomic chair.

First stop was Office Depot on/in West End. The manager, Mindy, took great care of me and I found both the heavy, austere, dark wood desk I wanted as well as the modern ergonomic chair I needed to make sure my Mr. Burns-like posture was held at bay for as long as possible. Thing is, this stuff is big, heavy and comes in pieces. What to do? Delivery and assembly.

The delivery part of the tale was a nightmare. Courier Express was a complete disaster: late, argumentative, disagreeable, and threw my heavy boxes into my (open) doorway and kept it moving. The whole point of delivery was having them deliver to where I needed the furniture set up. Didn't happen. Phone calls to their office/warehouse was about as effective as the Cubs in September.* Vowing a fatwa, I managed to figure out a way to carry the crazy heavy pieces through the ground floor, up the stairs and to my office. And then I waited for assembly. I was a bit scared.

I shouldn't have been. My guy was on time, polite, came with all his tools, and was ready to get to work. I posted up downstairs and let him have at it. In no time at all, I had an office chair that suited me to a tee (I'm sitting in it now). It seems like a small thing but it was so gratifying to finally have. Then came time for leviathan. This desk was no joke but as I listened to hammering, drills and the like, before I knew it, I had a large, stately desk that is going to serve me well for many years to come. I was extremely impressed with the speed with which he worked. I offered water but he had his own. This guy was good. AND, he put all the mess back in the boxes which significantly cut down on my clean up. I would use ARS again and again for my big furniture assembly projects. Why do it yourself when you can pay a pro to do it better than you could?

*I got my money back for the (non)service.

Tim & the Pro-Imports Crew took care of our vehicle and I felt that his invoice was fair and reasonable given the circumstances.  

Tim also filed all the required paperwork with the warranty company and went to bat for us when he thought the warranty company should pay additional sums towards the repairs

Every interaction was pleasant and straight forward.  I was never left guessing on the status of the repairs or the cost.

Highly Recommend.
Very friendly staff. All of the food was authentic and freshly made, as you can see the chef in the kitchen cooking everything (assuming you get the right seat). Will definitely return!

Beware:  BED BUGS.  My daughter stayed here for 3 nights last week, checking out on Thursday, 11/1.  She was training in Deptford for a new job, and the company put her and several other trainees up at the Fairfield Inn. Renovation was taking place in parts of the hotel. As other reviews have stated, there was an unpleasant odor of mold. My daughter cut her foot the first night on a broken off piece of metal from the base of the bed in the room. The hotel sent someone up to file off the sharp piece after she reported it.  Luckily, her tetanus shot is current.  Another evening, she came back to the hotel from training and went into the bathroom, almost falling due to water covering the floor. Apparently, several other rooms were also flooded.  She reported this, and was moved to another room.  In the meantime, a fellow trainee was bitten by bed bugs in her hotel room, which caused an allergic reaction, sending her to the ER (on her birthday, no less).  She took a picture of one of the bed bugs. The hotel allowed the woman to stay an extra night free of charge in order to treat her clothing/belongings so she wouldn't take the bed bugs back to her home on Thursday. My daughter called me in tears Thursday morning.  Her husband had stayed with her the previous night and discovered bites all over his body when he returned home to Philadelphia that morning. My daughter was panicking that her suitcase might be infested, and could do nothing about it as she needed to be in training all day.  I called Nisha, the manager at the Fairfield Inn, and asked that something be done; e.g. send someone to my daughter's nearby training site to pick up her suitcase and inspect the contents then treat them if infested.  At first, Nisha said there was not a bed bug problem at the hotel.  When she found out that I knew about the trainee that had gone to the ER due to bed bug bites, she said she could not discuss that. Nisha said there was nothing they could do about my daughter's possible infestation. She said she and another hotel employee had gone through my daughter's hotel room (Room 123) and not seen evidence of bed bugs. Since she had been less than honest about the bed bug problem, I had little faith in her word. I ended up having to drive from Philadelphia to the training site and going through my daughter's suitcase in the parking lot. It was hard to ascertain if there was an infestation as most of my daughter's clothes were black, so I piled everything in a large black trash bag.  When I took my daughter home, we washed and dried everything on high heat that we could.  Now we must just wait and see if her house is infested as a result of her stay at the Fairfield Inn. I called the Marriott corporate office and filed a complaint. I would NEVER stay at this hotel. Obviously, from the last few years of bad reviews, they are still not seriously addressing important health and safety issues that affect their customers.

Amazing dinner!!! Chef Charlotte bought the veggies that day at the Farmers Market and made the most amazing southern comfort food from it. Flank steak with cimichurri sauce and fabulous fried chicken with cream gravy, roasted butter potatoes, fried okra and squash casserole that was inspired. Not to mention an amazing happy hour! You had me at $3 mimosas. Hidden gem!! Call ahead to see what Chef Charlotte is making.

Dr Young is excellent and takes the necessary time needed. She's usually on time and her staff is nice. Watch the billing since they tend to bill and insurance hadn't been billed properly multiple times.
Service is a bit long. My order was mixed up. I did enjoy the homeade sausage biscuit.  The inside looks interesting. It seems like a hipster spot. Nothing special.
We had our first visit by invitation and it was awesome! The service was great and they did a fantastic job with the new location! So happy they built here!
The best atmosphere and staff! The quesadillas are amazing as well as their fresh sandwiches. I love that the beer menu is constantly rotating

I just searched Brothers Cafe on Google Maps to get their address for my spreadsheet and the picture on Google Maps is very bright with smiling people.  I'm not afraid to say that I was afraid to go into Brother's Cafe.  It was raining so it was dark outside and there was no natural light.  We are quarantined so there weren't a lot of people on the street.  I am glad I went inside.  Everyone was as nice as could be including the policeman that was getting his lunch.  I got the Salmon cheesesteak.  $16 but it was darn tasty. The sauce was heavenly.  Eye-catching smoothie descriptions.  Very good overall experience.

This place is just super!  It's the go-to brunch spot.  Last time, we had a Deal Chicken voucher, so it was an even better deal.  I recommend the Bloody Mary.  I like the scrambles, but most recently I had the vegan biscuits and gravy.  It was yummy!
They've expanded, so there's not as long of a wait-time.

Very comfortable and put together establishment! The place seems clean and well taken care of! The bathrooms were kind of gross and too small. The food and drink options were great. I'm not sure why but I ordered the nachos and went home with a pounding headache and was very ill for the rest of the day. Not sure if the ingredients were expired or if the meat was sketchy but I guess I can't enjoy the food here anymore, it was a very uncomfortable experience!

20 minute wait, no one in line. Always a super long wait. Guy had headphones in and super rude. Literally just ignored us as we sat at the window for 10 minutes when our drinks were ready. Didn't say a word, just handed us the drinks and we left. No words exchanged. Super unprofessional

I went for the first time last night for Hot Pot and I can't believe I've never taken advantage of the experience before. The restaurant is in the heart of china town and although not a huge, has space for larger parties as well as booths for smaller parties. A unique touch is the conveyor belt of toppings rotating in-between seating booths. 

Although the restaurant is centered around their Waygu beef in all varieties and preparations (even in the form of sushi), they have options for vegans! I'm a pescatarian so I chose the mushroom soup broth base(which is vegan), the seafood medley and the vegetable medley. My soup base had a variety of mushrooms and a really nice flavor. The seafood medley consisted of shrimp, mussels, clams, cod fish, and lobster tails. The vegetable medley consisted of romaine lettuce, spinach, baby bok choy. In addition to the main selection, I selected from the conveyor belt raw eggs which marinated in the broth was delicious. 

What really stood out about this restaurant was the presentation of the food and the service (Way was amazing as well as everyone else that was consistent in coming past our table to make sure we were full on water and happy with our meal). Although I would consider the restaurant to be casual, the foods presentation is on par with a 3 star Michelin restaurant, truly an experience. Whatever your expectations are, this restaurant truly will deliver and exceed them.

Family owned and operated for years in the heart of Swarthmore. The owners are pleasant, live in town and take great pride in providing  good food, coffee and baked items to their community.  
Their menus are imaginative and varied. Can't beat the soups or  the heat at home dinners. Their baked goods are reminiscent of days gone by.
They have this chocolate cakelike cupcapke with vanilla icing that is to die for.
Cookies are great. Muffins too. The coffee is good  and hot
I don't live in town but on the other side of the school district and I regularly drive here for a meal

It was a Thursday. I needed a custom 4 tiered cake delivered to a 500 person Shutterfest Expo event at the St Louis Union Station Hotel the following Tuesday night. I frantically called several bakeries with the slightest hope I can get it done with such short notice. I was losing hope until I found Celebrating Life Cakes and spoke with Sue. To my surprise, she gladly took my custom order in without hesitation and was so pleasant to work with from start to finish! (This was on Easter weekend, too!). Amazing.

I gave Sue a general idea of what I was looking for in terms of design & color for the cake. She quickly drew up a sketch just several hours later, and we were in business. She provided great ideas when I didn't know what I wanted, and took it upon herself to look up the event website to match the cake colors with the event's branding -- huge help. 

I ordered a 4 tiered cake as well as additional sheet cakes: chocolate, vanilla, and red velvet. I was nervous about the delivery, considering it was at a hotel during a busy evening event, but the delivery was very prompt and followed direction to the T. The cake was in perfect condition, looked amazing, and tasted GREAT! It completely wowed everyone (see photo). 

I can't thank Sue & team enough for taking this order in on such short notice and executing it so well. Completely exceeded my expectations and definitely recommend them to anyone looking for an awesome cake both in aesthetics/creativity & taste, great team, and reasonable pricing!

We went here before a friend's birthday and were very promptly served. It was a cute little place and it was very accommodating for us! Our waiter was very attentive and even recommended us a good wine to pair with our meals!

Seafood Ravioli- Off menu
This dish was wonderful and had a great combination of lobster, shrimp, and scallops. The sauce was a little thick and slightly too salty for my pallet. The noodles were also a little thick and over cooked as noodles were breaking off my fork. But the filling was outstanding. It makes up for the rest because it was a delight, the meat was not overly salty and had the perfect mixture of seafood.
Great seafood restaurant with a romantic and comfortable atmosphere. Food is flavorful!

Stoped in here just because I had to park near by. But I'm a coffeeholic so I had to stop in. I got a decaf breve latte. The coffee was perfect. They serve there own Bibo Coffee. My Latte had great flavor and nice texture. I would definitely cone back.

Excellent...designed 2 kitchens for me and helped me find a contractor.  Paul passes on his discount for granite, etc. onto customers rather than keeping it for himself.  Saved me money in many different ways.  He also has a history as a contractor so he knows what will work and what won't work.  Would refer him to anyone.

I needed new over the door hooks to screw into a combo jewelry closet/mirror that I have & when my boyfriend & I went in to get them it was like we were avoided by every employee possibly. Thankfully he has some knowledge about what may have worked, but every time we started to approach an employee it was like we were invisible or that they were in too much of a hurry to help other customers. We get it, we're college kids who can't drop 100s to 1000s of dollars on larger items in here but that doesn't mean you can't even point us in the direction of the right aisles for these hooks. The garden center redeemed itself though; I have so many plants for my dorm room that it's like a mini jungle, but this summer a lot of them outgrew their pots so I found a bunch here for a decent price plus a new penta in such a pretty dusty pink that I'm excited to see grow. The guy checking us out in the garden center was also super nice, almost makes up for everyone else avoiding us & bumps my rating up to 3 stars just because of how great he was.

What once was Sage, had now been re-branded. Same look inside. 

Had the salmon, it was also served in a bowl & over potatoes, which would not have been a preference for myself. But the salmon was cooked to perfection.  I wish they would have listed potatoes in their menu, as I would have subbed it out. 

My partner had a burger; it was cooked well, served in a black bun. Which the server told us about. 

The service was great, management checked on us twice.

I'd come again, just sub out the salmon.
I love their Bunker salad and the cozy environment. This place reminds of some of the cafes in DC.

I'm leaving a two because I didn't eat here but had a poor experience nonetheless. Had made a reservation for a pretty large party (was a dinner for a work retreat). We were all super excited to eat there given the reviews. When we arrived, one of the staff members borderline yelled at me, saying I had called and changed the reservation to a later time. This was false. They then yelled at me, claiming that someone else called and changed it on our behalf, also false. We waited outside for half an hour and we're then finally seated. The server was rude with us (I guess they were annoyed that they weren't ready for our reservation??). As we were about to order, I spotted a small sign that said "cash only". Being there for work and using the work CC, we had to leave. Overall an unpleasant experience. So be warned, cash only! And triple check your reservation with the staff.

I've been to the Brewery many times and each visit is worse than the one before. The very first time I was there was just for drinks. We sat at the bar and had some quesadillas which were decent. Pretty pleased overall. One of the next times I was there was for dinner. I had their veggie flat bread pizza which was sub par at best. Not very flavorful and the flat bread was really soggy...eww. The last time I was there was a Thursday night and it was absolutely empty however there was a dj blasting dance music right next to the bar. The only person dancing was a 40ish year old woman and although she was really enjoying the music no one else was...at all. Needless to say, we left shortly after arriving. Having to yell in an empty just doesn't make sense. 
So far, the Brewery has been hit or miss for me. Definitely love their Manayunk Lager but not enough to go there often.

They only have 4 tables for outside eating but our server was amazing and very nice the food was good and I recommend this place and give them your time they are trying to make it during these trying times. Oh and they are dog friendly which is always a plus with me! Nice local hangout spot.

Went to Pub 1922 prior to attending a little league baseball game this week. Found out they have a pretty decent happy hour menu with drink and food specials. Didn't have any of the beer specials this trip, but we did order food from the happy hour menu. We had the quesadilla and bbq pork sliders with just soda/tea to drink. Quesadilla was just ok, but the bbq pork was fantastic! The specials were even large enough to split with 2 bbq sliders on one plate & 4 pieces of quesadilla on the other. We think the 2 sliders & fries would be plenty. Back to the bbq pork - tender, tasty bbq, with a pickle and onion ring, and piled high. Don't miss this one . . . and only $5. Service was good - drinks came quickly and refilled during the meal - food came out hot & fresh. Improvement from last visit Pub 1922 - keep it up!

The people who work here are very strange. I'm not sure if it's a rude thing, but I had to remove the items of my basket (not cart) to the belt for her to start cashing me out. Very odd selection, typical Broad Ripple atmosphere.

Wasn't it the early 90's when Hyatt Hotels were the latest and greatest with their atrium and new age vibe? So upscale and sleek. That was then, people aren't as easily impressed these days and the Hyatt Regency  name doesn't invoke images of grand living. Actually, this particular one invokes images of Katrina damage and how long it took them to even decide to reopen. But that's another story.

Rooms are typical of hotels this age...on the small side with small bathrooms. This one is next to the stadium and if you're going for a game, it's a good place to stay. But it's a good long walk to the river or the French Quarter. The best thing about this hotel ... in my opinion ... is that it houses a John Besh restaurant (Borgne).

Don't get me wrong...this isn't a awful place to stay. It's just at the bottom of my list. Mainly due to location and plain vanilla big box hotel rooms. It's also on the expensive side.
The gelato here is delicious and homemade! You absolutely cannot go wrong with this place!

Best tacos and guacamole are the best in the downtown area. Margaritas are the best I've ever had. Service is outstanding and everyone is friendly. You tend to wait a bit longer than other places for a table but the wait is worth it. Can't go wrong with this place if your going for a night out on the town. My favorite time to go is in the summer when you can sit outside. Fun atmosphere and great entertainment.

We had a great time at Stumpy's. I loved the setup compared to other axe throwing places that I've been - each group has their own private section with couches. The staff was also very nice and helpful. Our only disappointment was that Stumpy's website says that you cannot BYOB (beer & cider) because they have a pour wall. However, we arrived to learn that they are not currently permitted to serve alcohol because their permit had been revoked. I wish that would have been updated on their website, because we would've brought our own if we had known. Otherwise, it was a good experience.
Very friendly service, but overpriced for what was served and I'm not sure if all the flavor combinations really worked well.
Awesome food and service. Went for breakfast and had the fruit crepes, I wanted to lick the plate!! My husband had the lobster bennie it had chunks of lobster, very good.

Be warned- a RATatoulli was sighted by my group scurrying around the restaurant as we finished our meal. The staff showed absolutely no concern and dismissed us saying it must have come from the construction outside?!!? There was no apology and no offer to provide reimbursement for a terrible experience!
Cassidy is flipping amazing! I appreciate her service and kindness! One of the best experiences I've had.
Amazingly delicious, welcoming & cozy. Food was great. We did breakfast, lunch & dinner on different days & all were spectacular. Staff very welcoming & friendly. We felt right at home.
Been going here for nearly 3 decades. Food is fresh and surprisingly good. Excellent selection... Don't miss this way more than a typical diner's food.
Food is good but prices are very high for what you get. A cup of soup and half sandwich will run you $11. It's unlikely I will return simply because the prices.

I was a little hesitant on eating at the Boise Idaho location due to hit and miss reviews. For me and my family it was a great experience. We ordered 2 Outback steaks, cob salad and blooming onions. Nice portions, reasonable prices , fresh salads ,bread, and a great waitress " Karisa"  I told Karisa of the hit and miss reviews and she just did  her job keeping our drinks full and extra bread. Boise steak houses are way pricey and I got a lot for my buck at the Outback.

Very good food here! The tavern pizza (square) is special. The meatballs are also quite good. I was a little disappointed with the bread the prosciutto hoagie was served on. Tried the clams and wings, both very good, and the draft beer was great. This is a promising place that could be a real crowd-pleaser in this neighborhood. Seems as though they need a little more time to get their feet under them in terms of service. Definitely worth checking out.

Alex just finished a deep clean of our home. I came back to a spotless shiny place. It felt really good to walk into a house and not smell a ton of cleaning products which was different than other cleaners we've had. Past cleaning crews have left me choking upon re-entry into our home because of the numerous and "fragrant" products they used that aren't always safe for humans and pets.

Alex is much more careful about toxicity and the environment and only uses products that don't leave a filmy residue or a strong odor. We are particular about not breathing in or touching so called "fragrances" that many cleaning products employ. Alex uses products that still cleaned everything well but not ones that we worry will bother our lungs or skin. I believe she is newish to the Charleston area and that means her calendar isn't completely full yet--her pricing was comparable to other deep cleans we've done, but again with the added bonus of a green, environmentally friendly approach!

Did not sleep a wink. Our second floor room was terribly noisy all night. It sounded like an old wooden rollercoaster was launching from our wall every 5 minutes. When I called the front desk I was told it maybe the service elevator and it wouldn't be running during the night. While the traffic in that elevator slowed during the night it didn't stop. I went to talk to the front desk in the morning and was told that third party websites are booked onto second floor. I asked if that was code for, "you get less because you paid less."  Although, that was unconfirmed it seemed to be true. 
The rooms were clean and beds were comfortable. Location is great. Just wished they cared that my family was up all
night because our room was apparently in an elevator shaft.

Very good Thai food. Can order the pad thai without egg if needed. I got the order to go and it was ready when I got there. Staff was very friendly and restaurant appeared clean and orderly. Very beautiful inside. If you park in front of the restaurant don't hit the yellow poles while backing out. You can see the light pole quite clearly in your rear view mirror but the yellow posts protecting it are too short and everyone hits them.

We were here as a group of 11, in their private dining room. Five stars for service; the two servers we had managed to deliver every request and not interrupt the meeting.

Two stars for food. We had two sampler platters and I ordered the brisket plate with creamed corn. Easily the best thing I ate was the quesadilla from the platter, it was filled with delicious carne asada and cheese and was good. The pulled pork on the potato skins and whatever meat was in the sliders was dry, as was the brisket on my plate. The brisket was fall apart tender and I've had it once years ago and enjoyed it but this time was unbearably dry. Not sure what was with the servings we had but I actually went back for a two hour cold quesadilla instead of eating it...I asked for salt to amp up the creamed corn, but it barely helped. Literally opening a can of Green Giant would have been better. 

Perhaps I had a different experience since it was the end of the day (maybe the meat was reheated, drying it out?) and I was with a group, but overall, I wouldn't go back unless I was stranded at the hotel.

I was at a Duluth Trading Company store in Independence, MO at the beginning of the summer and loved it. I knew this store was a must see while I was out doing a bit of holiday shopping at Bass Pro Shops. Love the Duluth quality and this store is really a cool thing to have in St. Louis. I bought a couple of the No Yank Tanks because I love them and I'm sure I'll be back soon!

Such a fun, relaxing place to rest from the city outside. If you bypass the bar on the first floor and venture upstairs, the air conditioning is on and you can people watch on the street below. Food is tasty and the wait staff is super friendly. We visit this place every time we're in Philly!

Holy amazing sushi batman!!!! Dude!!! When you hear how rice is the main ingredient and the sushi is secondary, this place make me get that!!! Fricken amazing sushi!!! Small hole in the wall nothing to write home about but unreal sushi!!!!
Having the BEST clam chowder in ST Pete Beach!!! Friendly bartender Brittany, come and enjoy she's amazing and will take good care of you!!!

On a random whim, we wound up in the Turnersville location and were helped by Fran. Her no-pressure and pleasant style put us at ease immediately. She was super helpful and patient. Our next purchase will definitely be there and with Fran B. Look her up; you'll be glad you did. We are

I have had cheesesteaks from here before and they were fine in the past...

BUT was on a business trip last week and decided to try a chicken parm dinner.  Now, since I am from NJ and believe our italian food is superior[sarcasm], I called to ask a specific questions... drum role please... "Is your chicken parm made with a chicken cutlet?"  The answer I was given by the pleasant young woman was "yes"  however there was hesitation.  Hindsight being 20/20 I now understand she - the person working in the italian restaurant - probably had no idea what a chicken cutlet was.  

What arrived was totally GROSS!  A pan of overcooked sweet sauced spaghetti with three TRIANGLE shaped pieces of thick chicken (obviously deep fried) just thrown on top of it all.  Barely any cheese, more sweet sauce.

Gross, just gross.  I will NEVER order from here again.  I would rather eat a frozen chicken parm dinner that I can pick up from the grocery store.
Updating this to 5 Stars now due to a new dish on the menu: roasted brussel sprouts with purple mustard paired with a pear, almond and celery leaf salad. Delicious.

Was able to walk in on a Saturday night without reservations and got a table for 2 right away! Menu has tapas, sushi, pizza and specials. Lots of options to satisfy any craving you have. I had a hard time deciding so we ended ordering a few different tapas to share. The salmon special was delicious and enough for one person honestly. The pork belly was cooked perfectly on a bed of Mac and cheese and I could resist the loaded tots! Everything came out very quickly. We were in and out of there in no time! One thing I did not like was that there are only 2 unisex restrooms in the back to share.
the worst pad thai i ever have! the meat is not fresh and the taste is bad
Great food, service, and atmosphere.  It definitely brightens up that end of Chester Pike!

Due to the ever expanding chip seal repair here in the Treasure Valley I have received windshield damage on two vehicles in the last two months.  The damage consisted of four rock chips and one windshield in need of replacement.  

I contacted Tyler (Business Owner) through Yelp messaging and had my first rock chip repaired within a few days. Tyler arrived early during his suggested time window and he seemed much more confident than other technicians I had used in the past. 

Just two weeks later I found myself in need of a windshield replacement.  Once again Tyler set a high standard with the installation, quality and price of the windshield.  

While I don't look forward to having anymore rock chips I feel it is inevitable. Based on his repairs Tyler has earned a lifetime customer.

Let's put it this way. 
It is not authentic at all. (at the same time I saw some Indian customers - couples and families).
Yes, smb here called it upscale. It is upscale in American terms. But is it Indian? No masala chai?
It is fusion and it is delicious. The food presentation is great.
Got tiny quail (wasn't impressed),  fancy samosa, saag paneer (spinach with cheese) Yumm, and carrot cake.  (Saag panner was the best item I got). They charge extra for rice.
The service is really great: fast, super polite and high-energy.  The ambiance is nice. Don't remember if there was any music. The unisex restroom  confuses customers at first, but the design of it is really high-end..
The price for all of it was about $70

If you read Gambit's "Best of New Orleans:Food 2016" you'll find that one of the top three places for boiled seafood is Deanie's on Lake Avenue. If you also happen to care about the taste of your boiled seafood and not what Gambit readers/voters think is the best seafood, you'll do yourself a favor and walk over to Sid's instead. The shop and its staff may be small, but it's clean, high quality, and constantly churning out an array of boiled seafood that's being prepared outside as you wait.  I've had the crabs, and come back for the crawfish multiple times a month. For crawfish specifically you get a nice array of sizes, perfect seasoning, and a great price (it's a few cents cheaper if you pay with cash). So next time you're craving something boiled, do yourself a favor and stop by Sid's.
Awesome place.The food was amazing and our waiter Jose really made the experience all the better. I highly recommend it

Okay so I took my coworker here because anytime I'm in town I grab grub and a margarita here. I told her that the service isn't great, the servers don't listen, but that the food was good. Halfway through our meal I realize she's pushing her food around and turns out she had somehow gotten a tuna chimichanga. I don't think I even knew you would find tuna at a hole-in-the-wall Mexican place, however, I think they ordered Chicken of the Sea instead of chicken in the can. Through my hysterical laughter over such a funny thing I told the bartender and without saying anything to me he just took the plate away. I saw him hanging out at the corner of the bar and asked him what the outcome was and he said they don't deep fry fish.... To resolve the issue he said he would only charge me for the chimichanga and not the beans and rice. I told him that's not acceptable and I want to talk to a manager. Instead of calling the manager over to speak to me where I was sitting, He told me I had to go up to the front and talk to him. So I go up front in the manager begrudgingly agreed not to charge me at all for the meal. Absolutely ridiculous. Hysterical, but ridiculous.

If it were up to me I'd give this place 3 stars, but Chan loved it so I'll up it to 4.  We were here on a Sunday night in late May and the place was almost empty.   The bread and home  made olive oil was nice.   We shared an order of carpaccio and it was pretty good, I have yet to have bad carpaccio.  Chan had the lobster ravioli that was topped with a bunch of fried onion strings that I thought really overpowered the sauce and pasta, Chan liked it alot.   I had the  "Tagliata di Bue con Rugola e Tortino di Patate", sliced beef tenderloin with a potato tart, arugala, parm and truffle oil.  I found my dish bland, especially the potato tart which was basically hash browns sans salt.  The beef was cooked well.  Dessert was very good.   The restaurant certainly had enough charm to warrant a return visit.
Ed's Benedict was great! Bloody Mary also great. Very polite staff

This is the very edge of St Louis dining culture. They have taken Italian dining to an entirely new level, making a neighborhood Italian restaurant an elegant affair.  I have eaten here seven times in the last two months because I just cannot find another experience that parallels this one. Oysters, Duck Confit, Steak Tartar, Pork Bolognese - the menu changes at a fairly fast pace but it always has a feel of being the same place.

More than anything else though is their bartender Jeff.  He is making drinks there that rival any hip bar on either coast.  After you have a couple of his standard drinks you can tell him what you liked about them and he will whip up something special that fits your food and your taste.  

This is my favorite restaurant in St Louis. The price is high, but worth every penny- get reservations because once it fills in the evening the place never slows down.
Amazing service, friendly owners!  We get poke every Friday, they remember our order and are happy to see us!  The new location is clean, and we get the same amazing service as the Goleta location.
It's pretty good! Also right on the beach  The bar is kind of loud, so if you want peace, probably not the best. Burger was great, and service was fantastic!

Made a appointment,  days ahead, show up, waited pass appointment time, finally in pedicure chair, waited and waited, hot water turned cold, the received a rushed pedicure. Massage was a nothing, scrubbing heel barely happened, he was serving me and a the gal next to me, ridiculous. First time to this place, will be the last.

The staff here has been extremely helpful in caring for my dog with an extreme case of valley fever. They would call for updates and were very thorough in managing her pain. You can just tell that they care for the animals and will work in the best interest of your pet. I am very thankful for them!!

All  of a sudden...no AC, in Florida, while packing. Major bummer & totally inconvenient. I spoke to Dan in the morning & explained, AC had stopped with no prior problems.
This is a family owned & run business. Dan came out early afternoon, diagnosed & repaired the problem.
He was very professional & explained everything, so we understood what had happened & how he corrected the problem. I feel the price was fair & Dan was great & easy to work with.
Would definately use again.
What's a girl to do? Roll with the punches of home ownership & hope you get homest, good people to assist with repairs.
Great food and concept! So fun and really delicious. Had the maitake bao and actually liked it better than the KFC one which I was surprised by. But all were great

Went last night for valentines dinner. Had a reservation for 7, we were finally seated around 7:30. The hostess was very apologetic and friendly. We were given complimentary champagne while we waited. Unfortunately there wasn't a lot of room to wait so we and several other couple were basically hovering around the diners seated near the door. The ambience was cool.  The hostess again, while friendly, tried to open our $120 bottle of wine (that we saved for a special occasion) and destroyed the cork, my boyfriend had to intervene and save the day. 

The food. We ordered an oyster each, a cheese plate to share, and two different entrées, him the veal chop, and me the bass and duck. The oysters were fine at almost $4 each. The cheese plate and pairings were good at $12. And the entrees... Freaking terrible and about $35 each!!! The veal was almost raw while the duck was completely overdone and the fish was REALLY fishy while cooked properly.  The portions were tiny.  And the food was almost in edible.  The worst part though was these whole pickled onions that were served with the veal.  There were many of them mixed with the greens the veal was served with. I ate one and it was TERRIBLE!!!  I couldn't get the taste out of my mouth for the rest of the night.  

To summarize...we showed up, long wait to be seated, friendly hostess and wait staff, slow service, and BAD FOOD, we left $120 poorer and hungry still!!!  Nachos down the street saved the night. We will NEVER go back.
I will not be returning.  Very unprofessional.  First and last appointment was a year ago.
The food tasted ok, but the chicken in the fried rice was weird and spongy. I've been very sick ever since I ate it. I won't be back.

We loved working with Casino Party Experts!  They were great from start to finish.  From planning, to the event, and tear down ---everyone on the team is fun and professional.  Our team is raving about the event a week later and they are already asking us to book them again for next year.

Like Emily S. said, the concept is very cool.  There are about 50 wines you can try (1, 3 or 5 oz).  The prices are very expensive for the wine's they are.  The cheapest 1 oz. sample is $1.07.  Personally, I would prefere going to Vintage in Reno (same concept, better wine & prices...and you get free cheese while trying wine).

Wow, this place is truly great - but I wish everybody would stop classifying Bouligny Tavern as a Gastropub just because it has Tavern in its name.  It's not a gastropub - it's an upscale small plate food & drink place that has nice cocktails, a very nice wine list, and excellent food (but limited beers which pretty much negates the idea of calling this a gastropub).  The burrata & pesto bruschetta was outstanding and the gougeres were tiny and apparently multiply like rabbits but all 19 of the airy pastries were eventually consumed because they were just plain good.  The burger was close to perfect (just on the edge of being overseasoned for my palate but cooked perfectly and extremely tasty) while the spinach gnudi were also amazing - little spinach "meatballs" with a great tomato sauce and cheese that complemented them perfectly.

There are only about 30 seats at tables and probably half as many at the [busy] bar - it's a fairly good looking and trendy crowd of professionals which is not a bad thing and as long as you can find a seat you'll get great drinks and food.  Go for the great food, cocktails, and wine - it's a fantastic place that takes pride in everything (other than the service at times) and you'll enjoy whatever you get.

My mom and went here for brunch. I had the power wrap and my mom had the avocado toast. Both Walsh were great. The restaurants was clean and the hostess and server were following proper mask and safety measures were perfect. The tables were a safe distance apart. This was my first restaurant meal since the CIVID green phase was implemented. Both my mom and I felt the restaurant took care to make us feel safe while enjoying our wonderful meals and conversation.

This was a pleasant experience! There was a quiet, romantic-esque ambience. Upon arrival, we were instantly greeted and were advised that we could sit ourselves. Our waitress was very down to earth, and gave many recommendations including their specialty,  "the French Bread Hamburger"...of course this was what I ordered (w/fries), along with the cup of chili. 
For an appetizer we had the cheesesticks, which were really good. Grade A mozzarella fried to golden perfection, and served fresh out of the fryer! So cheesy and flavorful! I got mine served with ranch dressing, which just added to the greatness. 
I then received my burger and chili, and boy was it on. I can honestly say that this burger was really far better than I anticipated! The French bread was toasted and buttery, so it had that soft crunchy outside, but a warm chewy inside. The burger was VERY well seasoned, and I was surprised at all the flavor and juiciness of it! 
Now let me tell you about my absolute favorite part of the dinner was the chili!! This was the BEST chili I'd ever had! (Next to Ma's, and it's a close 2nd. ..don't tell Ma!). The flavor was spot on with saltiness and spice! My favorite part was the big chunks of perfectly seasoned ground beef! The bean to meat ratio was sheer perfection! Add the shaved cheese and ranch dressing, and I was in dinner heaven! 
This was a really great experience, and the only down side was one of the waitresses  although so sweet, was a little too chatty. ..and the owner wasn't the friendliest  (but it could've been a long night!)
I enjoyed my visit, and would definitely return again!

As a huge It's Always Sunny Fan I had to go here and was not dissapointed. The loaded gravy fries were excellent and more than enough for 2 people and Mac's tea was so tasty. So tasty and SO strong, would buy again ;) Would be nice if there was more it's always sunny stuff there but still happy to see it.
Great venue! Had a wait, but it was shorter than they anticipated and I just found a space at the bar for the wait! Staff is so friendly!

Let me give an UPDATED REVIEW for anyone attempting to gain employment opportunities at THIS STORE: Today I went with my friend to cash her DUNKIN DONUTS PAYROLL CHECK and the check cashing place informed her that they'd need to call the store to verify the check and verify that she was an employee of Dunkin. Well, THE VERY SAME MANAGER that I had issues with, LAWANDA RAINEY AKA ZEE answered the phone and LIED and stated that she had NEVER heard of my friend nor had anyone by her name EVER worked there and suggested that the check cashing place call the police (1754 South Hanley Rd) even though ZEE physically gave my friend her paycheck at 11:15AM on Friday morning. Well because of Zee lying, the police was called on my friend - When the police arrived, they called the store and LAWANDA RAINEY AKA ZEE (the lady with the meth teeth) repeated the same LIE to the police BUT the police who arrived had previously worked at THIS DUNKIN DONUTS and was well aware of the foolishness that goes on at THIS LOCATION. One of the officers contacted his sister, who is a district manager and SHE WAS ABLE TO VERIFY MY FRIENDS EMPLOYMENT AT THE DUNKIN LOCATED AT 1754 SOUTH HANLEY RD! THE POINT OF THIS UPDATED REVIEW IS TO WARN FOLKS THAT LAWANDA RAINEY AKA ZEE, THE STORE MANAGER WILL NOT ONLY BE RUDE TO THE CUSTOMERS BUT WILL LIE AND WEAPONIZE THE POLICE AGAINST THE EMPLOYEES SHE APPARENTLY HAS ISSUES WITH!! THIS STORE DEFINITELY NEEDS BETTER LEADERSHIP BC THIS WOMAN LAWANDA RAINEY AKA ZEE IS A DANGER TO THE COMMUNITY! If she's willing to go as far as LYING TO THE POLICE on an employee, what makes you as a customer trust that she's not doing foul things to your food or drinks? I am definitely going to pursue action against this store until THIS WOMAN - LAWANDA RAINEY AKA ZEE - is no longer employed at this store!

My 1st time here for lunch, the have a different menu for lunch and dinner. I had the pork bolognese gnocchi and grits. The gnocchi was awesome my only complaint is they don't give you enough, it's bigger than a tasting but smaller than an entree. However it's packed with flavor. If I could order a big cereal bowl full and eat it I would. The grits wasn't as good as I expected. Somewhat dry, not as flavorful considering it's cooked with Tasso which is a creole spiced ham, I wasn't getting any of that flavor profile at all. Not to take anything away from Cafe Dufrain, the grits that come with the shrimp and grits at fly bar is better executed. I will give Cafe Dufrain an A+ for having simple syrup, a definite plus when having iced tea.
Stopped in for lunch today. Food, service and decor was great! Unfortanately, the raw sewage smell as you walked in was a future deal breaker. Sorry

I went to Little Nest about 1 month ago to have one of their free Growing Bellies sessions to document my 8th month of pregnancy.  The receptionist and photographer were both great and I was pleased to get a really nice photo, free of charge, by later that night.  I was also surprised that I didn't get a sales pitch while I was there.  

I decided to schedule another session for 3 weeks later when I would be 37 weeks pregnant.  Our session was scheduled at 5:30 pm and the night before my session, I confirmed via their online system.  My mother and husband came as well, all of us leaving work early and driving over 30 minutes from our home to get to the appointment.  When we arrived, the studio was locked and dark.  I checked my email and saw that someone had written me at 330pm to tell me that she had to reschedule my appointment because the photographer was no longer available.  I wrote her back that I was very disappointed that no one called me as I do not obsessively check my email and it was a huge inconvenience (especially at this stage in pregnancy) to have to show up to an appointment that I didn't know was cancelled.  Its been a week later and I received no follow up reply.  Based on this experience, I would not recommend this studio to others.

This place is just ridiculous.  I bought a Groupon for six laser hair removal treatment.  I had my first treatment in April.  In May, three days before my appointment, they called and told me they had to cancel my appointment and to reschedule online.  I was miraculously able to get in a week after my original appointment time.  Then I didn't even get my treatment until an hour after my scheduled time.  I thought ok, no big deal stuff happens.  Next appointment was at the end of June.  Once again they called a week before my appointment to let me know they had to cancel and they weren't accepting appointments for laser hair removal until after Labor Day and to go online and reschedule.  At this point I was going to be well pass the 6-8 week recommended gap between appointments.  I got on that day to reschedule.  Next available day was October 29th.  My first two laser treatments were essentially useless now and I wouldn't be able to get full results with my remaining 4 appointments.  To top things off I got a call yesterday telling me my appointment was once again canceled.  

Is this how all their services are, or is this just for Groupon customers?
Does this place even need a yelp review? Katie and her team are amazing. Truly a Grade A group of trainers who will kick your a** and stretch you out the right way.
I love their smokey brisket and shredded chicken, and the Messy Fries are real bomb!
Stood at the window for 5 minutes.  Nobody noticed.  Left.  Well done assholes.  Enough said.

Waste of time and money!  When you go through the wash you can tell wash cycle is a lot shorter then other car washes and your car is rushed through for no reason leaving your car dirty.  Employees seem not to care that you paid $20 for a wash and immediately see dirt spots all over you car, no management is around to speak to, this place is a joke!

Got another tattoo done about 10 months ago. This one was rough for me, I haven't really wanted to talk about it, but it came out so perfect I just have to add a review. 
I worked up another tattoo after my father passed. Personally spent 100+ hours finding fonts, doing preliminary designs, and then lots and lots of fixing and tweaking. Eventually I had it perfect and went down to see Steve again. Set up an appointment got some gorgeous work done. It came out exactly how I wanted and is simply perfect. 
A variation of a Goethe quote "Nothing is more important than this day" with a small green triangle as the punctuation.

I also have to say that I sent my friend Trish down there as well after she had a bad experience with another vendor in the area and she said that Brian was awesome, made her feel very comfortable and she loves the work!

Go to Copperfish!!!  I really like this restaurant.  Surprised that it isn't always packed, though. I would really hate to see this restaurant fizzle out.  The concept is great, the food has always been wonderful, featuring an exciting menu.  I have never had anything not measure up here!  The lobster was amazing, the beef carpaccio pushed me a little past what I usually go for and has become a dish that I dream about!  The smoked oysters are a must!  Mussels are fabulous and a really great deal, the fresh salad from the organic lettuce wall is delicious and all of the ingredients are fresh and bright.  The decor is really beautiful and makes it perfect for a special night or any kind of occasion like a rehearsal dinner, date night or celebration.  I have only had to wait for too long for my food one time.  The waitstaff is professional and knowledgeable.  Please, go to Copperfish!
Great location (aka down the street from our home hehe) lots of parking. Famoso is one of our favourite pizza places and it never disappoints. Prices are great also. Affogatos are a must post dinner.

Didn't live up to the hype. My husband and I went for the first time a few years ago for our wedding anniversary dinner and haven't been back since. The food and wine selection were great, service on the other hand.....when I told our server what I decided on for dinner she said, "excuse me?" I told her my selection again and she said "wow, I'm just really surprised you would have selected that" with a laugh. What?! Did I select something outrageous? No it was one of their poultry entrees on the menu. Granted, I know it's Berns and you are "supposed to" order steak. But really Berns server? Do I need the extra commentary and your opinion on what I'm ordering? Honestly, I'd rather go a mile down the street to Bella's, have better service and a better meal.
Suzie did an incredible job with my full set/ gel manicure!! First visit and will definitely return!

Not a huge fan of microwaved bacon and eggs. Not very fresh or a tasty product. Cashier took my order and didn't ask if I wanted anything else just gave me my total. I won't be back as there are plenty of other small businesses that serve breakfast sandwiches and bagels that blow this place away.

I've gone here for coffee, lunch, and dessert when visiting a good friend who lives down the street.  The first perk: the stellar location with eastern state looming ominously outside the front doors. 

Their menu is jampacked with organic fare, and they offer a hell of a lot of vegan options:  sandwiches, wraps, smoothies, muffins, cakes, cupcakes, cream cheese, etc. - all vegan friendly.  I can say for sure that The Slammer  (lettuce, tomato, vegan meatballs, and guac) was different, messy, and delicious.   I can also say their vanilla soy latte and vegan carrot cake are creamy and flavorful - my non-vegan friend and I had to alternate spoonfuls to keep things fair. 

But I 100% recommend visiting this cafe, I wish I had one of these in my neighborhood, I'd for sure be a regular. And will be returning.
The tour was very interesting. I especially enjoyed learning the history of the company. The tour guides were knowledgeable and personable.

Today's visit was 5 star all the way. Excellent service while sitting at the bar. The beer was cold and perfect - I asked for a shandy and it was so good. The blackened mahi fresh catch sandwich tasted so fresh I thought they must have just caught it this morning. It came with coleslaw and beans & rice. The bun was soft and fresh too. A really great meal.

The bartender was not very knowledgeable about what was offered. We went for drinks after lunch at Fogo, and the patron next to me at the bar had an issue with her salad. 
Drinks were quite high priced.

This place was recommended by several people, so we decided to eat here for our last dinner in Nashville. We were also told to sit at the Chef's table because of the awesome view of the kitchen. The food was really well-prepared, flavorful and delicious. I wish the portions were a little bigger, but it was what I expected for a fine dining restaurant. We got the mussels appetizer, which was a very different but enjoyable flavor for mussels. For entrees, we ordered the lamb, scallops, and pork chop. Everything was delicious and beautifully presented...almost too pretty to eat! I would definitely recommend coming back for a special event or date.

Absolutely love these guys!  They always get me in and out fast for oil changes (which is awesome with young babies), and hook me up with great coupons for tires.  Johnathan even knew my name when I walked in the door, it was awesome. Definitely ask for him!
I've been using them for the past 10 years with all my cars, and only strayed once by going to Costco (and completely regretted it).  Goleta is my favorite shop, although Milpas is a close second.
Wow! What an experience! Great food, service and vibe. We were celebrating an anniversary and Sbisa delivered. We'll be back for the good food and all the Kenny G covers. Mhmm

I really like New Castle Farmers Market, this place is one of the reasons why! I usually get the combo special #2. It comes with a sausage sandwich, hot or mild, chips, bbq or regular, macaroni salad and small fountain soda you can upgrade to a larger size however. This place has some of the best sausage around with fast service and friendly helpful staff. They have fresh cut fries and other fried goods such as vegetables. They also have turkey sausage and cheese steaks!

With a Peruvian friend who rated this authentic. Enjoyed the perfectly fried fish and seafood (Jalea) plate with a tasty yellow sauce. Free chips came with a wonderful green sauce which we had to ask for more. Great flavors here.

Very happy with my Federal Donuts trip. I stopped in before my bus ride home and snagged a few for the ride. These cake donuts are perfectly fluffy while still maintaining a nice density with a good crunch on the outside. The flavor of batter might be the tastiest I've ever had. It was really great. The hot and fresh strawberry lavender and vanilla spice are perfectly dusted with a sweet flavoring. And the chocolate sea salt and blackberry walnut were also nice treats. The chocolate glaze soaked into the cake and made it extra moist. The cold brew was delicious as well. Looking forward to stopping by again next time I'm in Philly.

This PE is located inside the Welcome Center of Delaware. Easy access off the highway. 
Located all the way to the end of the facility, you go through other options, however.. I knew Panda Express was the one I would go for. 
The line  as pretty long, but moved quickly. Plenty of staff doing the most at keeping things fresh and hot. 
Orange chicken is a stable of PE, and my other favorite is the Beijing beef over rice.
4.5 Came here for Father's Day brunch and the food was absolutely amazing. The service was not the best, but eventually got better. I'll definitely be returning.
