We've stopped by Rooster's Kitchen a few times now and have loved our experience each time. Anastasia was our server twice and she's simply the bomb. Their Damn Good Grilled Cheese is both crispy and gooey good, and we can't stop ordering their customizable Mac n Cheese. I tried the Buddha Bowl for a healthier option this last time and it did not disappoint. They have an excellent selection of bottled/canned and draft beer as well as appropriately spaced seating for COVID restrictions. They even set out a few tables outside for dining. We've visited here at busy dining times and have never had to wait for a table. Parking is either out front on Mass Ave in metered parking, or behind the apartment complex across the street. We hope you love it as much as we do!

I run in here a few times a year.  I once had a photo order that went unprinted for weeks.  Then they told me the printing machine just wasn't on and wasn't working.  The checkout line tends to move fast, which is a plus.  Staff are friendly too.
Great food and great service. I ordered lunch Chicken Club and hubby ordered breakfast French toast Combo. We both enjoyed  our selections. We would definitely go again. Thank

Negative stars. Avoid for your own sanity. This was hands down the worst use of rewards points possible. 

1. Unacceptably understaffed. One lady mans the front desk, and shares her one nighttime staff member or handyman with the neighboring hotel during frequent emergencies.
2. Facilities in massive disrepair. They will tell you it is currently being renovated, so listen to them and stay away until they are *absolutely finished* with renovations, whenever that is. Heaters rattle loudly or are broken in some rooms. If something is broken, and a maintenance guy comes, he may leave without cleaning up the mess behind him. Doors will not close/lock easily or automatically in many rooms due to unprofessionally reapplied door paint. Curtains are worn down with unexplained holes. Leaking hallway ceiling. Some faucets jut out from the wall.
3. Incomplete cleanings between guests and hastily applied bedding. I may just be lucky but I have never stayed in a hotel where the staff repeatedly fails to clean a room completely or properly put the fitted sheet onto the mattress.

There were so many more episodes during my 5 nights in hell. But just trust me on this one and book anywhere but here.

Just left there and it wasn't that great. Our server wasn't personable, and very slow, the food was sub par especially for the price. The food is way overpriced. They have new croutons that taste like stale bread and no more mashed potatoes.  Needless to say we won't be going back.
This was my favorite restaurant for years.  It's just not the same anymore.  We had a bad experience and gave it 2 more tries.  I won't be going back.

It is definitely best to visit this location at off-peak times to avoid  r e a l l y  long lines!

You may even want to swing into neighboring Hubbard and Cravens and pick up some fuel to sip on during your wait. :)

Bonus points if you can get the staff to smile during your transaction! From my experience, it's a tall task at this location.

Wow! This company has close to 300 reviews and has one star! Says it all. 
We were told we had to wait close to two weeks for a technician to come out to set up WiFi. Two weeks pass and no one ever came out! I took off work to stay home during the four hour window and no one ever showed up. I cancelled the service before it was even set up. Horrible customer service!

As inexperienced appliance installers, we wanted to buy something that would connect our used dryer to the wall, which had a different shape.  We went through three different people asking how we could make it work and lots of staring at various wall adapters.  The guy wasn't sure it was even possible, so we left, frustrated that we had wasted $200 on a used dryer.  
A few days later we stopped by Lowe's.  The appliance guy there immediately knew what we needed and explained how to install the new wires.  All that drama for a $20 fix. Home Depot was no help.

Also, Home Depot awards military discount, but has to have the manager approve it.  We waited for the manager for nearly 10 minutes while checking out, just for her to look at my ID.  The checkers aren't idiots, they can read an ID.

The wings are good, the bar is alright, the atmosphere is ok, but everything else was pretty terrible. In addition to the wings, we ordered pulled pork and brisket nachos, and we couldn't even finish either because the meat was tasteless and the BBQ sauce that came on the side was awful. The layout of the place is a complete mess due to the lack of a seating, and disorganized "parking lot." I think the place is meant to be a bar, not a restaurant, in which case they should change the name because it's misleading.

Perhaps they were having an off night, but we aren't likely to return. If you do go there, we found only the wings are worth ordering.

I went here at the spur of the moment and it's closer to me. My pedicure was nice, got a pretty color and all. Then came time for my manicure and I wanted dip powder. I've been getting dip powder for a good minute now and I always refuse the drill,hasn't been an issue. My opinion if you can't do nails without relying on the drill then you just can't do nails period.
I am Deaf, and I told them just as much. So it becomes frustrating when they keep trying to communicate with masks on. Well I sat down for my manicure and she whipped out the drill. I started shaking my head indicating that I do not want the drill. She kept trying to insist on it. I let her know those make my nail beds hurt for weeks, I don't do drills. Another lady came over and kept talking to me, I shook my head letting her know I couldn't hear nor understand her. She got an attitude and yanked her mask down and said "no drill no dip" I said wow ok got up and indicated that I wanted to pay for my pedicure. 
The manager was then summoned and she came to me and mentioned about her doing my manicure instead. I said no thank you I didn't like your employee's attitude I wanted to pay for my pedicure and leave. 
Now what do you propose nail technicians did before the drill???? I'm paying you for a service I want...not the other way around.

I will never go there again

I remember when i used to like this theater i don't know why they had to change it i guess after going to oldsmar AMC you can see the big differece. for one they don't make me feel like a thug they are checking purses and everything you carry once you go in seriously? they want to make sure you will buy from them their expensive crap! and the way the theaters and movies are staged is so you can only see one movie. AMC is totally ok with you roaming as you please that's a good movie theater my favorite and never will go again to the regal one anymore.
Pulled pork sandwich was awesome yesterday....back today for wings!! Sides of broccoli salad, potato salad and baked beans are top choices!

After Pat's we went to Geno's.
It was somewhat better. The bread was tastier, the onions more savory and the steak more tender. We went for whiz directly. 
It was great in a fat ass artery clogging way. Deeeelicious junk food.
So  good in fact so we took two to go-one for the trip home and one for a friend.
Not so into the obnoxious decor and flagrant cop ass kissing tributes but the steaks were good.
And they gave us free Joey Vento pens. Yay. Gag.

http://www.genosteaks.com
I've had a lot of donuts but these were the best!!!! I was recommended the caramel cinnamon and it was out of this world good!!!! The store was impeccably clean and the server was so friendly.

I stopped by to have a late lunch, as I seated myself at the bar, the bartender ignored me for an approximate 6 to 8 minutes, a simple " hello ill be with you " momentarily, would have been acceptable. When I finally got to order my food it was dry and you could tell it was not served in proper time, it was a bit cold just as the female bartender. I expected better service being this is a more an upscale place to have a quick bite to eat.
Everytime I come here I get great service! The pizzas amazing! The people are fantastic! I love coming here!

Delicious! I have been really into their vegan ice creams lately l. April they had a couple of special flavors that were vegan. One was lemon with sprinkles. I didn't think the sprinkles would add anything as I never really understood sprinkles, but they gave the ice cream a really nice texture. Their passion fruit vegan ice cream is also delicious. 

Every monthly flavor I have tried is incredible. Roris is delicious ice cream!
Kara and Daria help me out with surprises flowers for my mom!  They were wonderful to work with and assorted the arrangement for me.  Thanks guys.

Simple, but clean motel.  

Reasonably priced. Each room is decorated by a local artist. There are bikes that you can rent to ride around SB for free. Good location.

I will be back for sure.

Visited the place at the new year's eve. Staff was rude and drinks were below average. Again staff was rude....
Sorry one little bad experience is enough for 1-star i will give a 2nd chance then we will see...

Sweet spot in temple terrace, Tampa. Lunch deals are a must. My party tried the following:

Chicken summer rolls with peanut sauce- fresh vegetables and the sauce was light but packed with flavor 7/10

Volcano chicken- great portion with crispy tempura chicken with spicy sauce 8/10

Crispy duck rice- very well seasoned duck with soya chilli sauce 8/10

Devils rice- wonderfully flavored ground chicken with peppers topped with a flash fried egg 8/10

Visit this place! Great prices for good food.
My wife and I enjoyed walking through the museum and taking it all in. I would recommend going for anyone who hasn't been before. Definitely do the "Beyond All Boundaries" film.

My son and his family including 3 children 8 to 13 were in town overnight on a Sat.  I called at the last minute and they accommodated us, even though when we got to the restaurant, there was a full house.  I have eaten here before so knew the food was delicious.  The service was excellent--very sweet to my grandkids--making sure we were happy with everything.  We had the tuna carpaccio and mozzarella,basil&tomato for starters; then my son had the veal porterhouse (a special) and others had the chicken parm, gnocchi with wild mushrooms, ravioli and I had the best chicken marsala ever--and I am an afficionado of that dish. They have wonderful specials.  Between Tuesday and Thursday, they have a prix fixe menu which I have sampled several times.  Do yourself a favor and give it a try.  My son, who now lives in Boston, said that he couldn't believe we now had such fine dining in Roxborough!

Omg! I love this place! This place is super fun! I like that you get to try different beers. They give you a wrist band and put it up to the z on the panel and you pour as much as you want.
 The pizza is good and the beer is good. They have a great deal where you can pick three things 1 slice of pizza, salad, and 12 ounce beer for under 10 dollars. 
My favorite pizza has been pepperoni and banana peppers. The pear and gorgonzola cheese is also really good. If you go get the not your dad's root beer! 
So good!

Ate here on a Sunday night with spouse and daughter #3. Place looked a bit odd from the outside, very small and crowded, cheap furnishings. I didn't want to go inside. Then I stood outside and looked at the menu and saw a) vegetarian b) middle eastern good, and c) interesting choices. Then inside I saw outstanding beer selections, so how bad can it be?
I was very pleasantly surprised. Special soup was a Hungarian caraway soup that my wife/daughter LOVED, I found the caraway flavor overwhelming. We had a pick 3 hummus (baba ghanoush, hummus-olive and hummus-garlic) which were simply outstanding. Entrees were very tasty, I had a combo of salads (carrot, tabbouleh, felafel) which were tasty. I would definitely return.
We were told that the chef had suddenly quit a few days earlier and that the son of the owner was filling in, no noticeable damper on food quality or service. Well done Meze!

Easily one of the worst meals I've had out in the last decade.  Arrived to find a sign on the door saying dining for customers with reservation only.  I looked in and the restaurant was mostly empty, so I went in and asked if I my wife and I could eat inside.  After some hesitancy, the hostess conferred with another person and said she would allow it.  The prior reviewers comments about the staff being rude were spot on.  Not a single courtesy throughout the evening, entree dishes were brought to the table without comment, and it seemed like the staff didn't want to be there.  Or want us there.  My wife's egg roll was very greasy, so greasy in fact that she needed to use a second napkin.  She disliked her main dish of Honey Walnut Jumbo Shrimp and didn't eat it.  My all-you-can-eat sushi was below par.  The sashimi was cut small and was shaped oddly.  The sushi rolls were disappointing.  Wegman's sushi is way better than this.  About the only highlight was the green tea ice cream.  It was great, albeit the staff brought a very small serving.

DO NOT MOVE HERE!!!!!!

A few months after I moved in a resident in the apartment next to mine had their ceiling fall in due to water damage and it caused massive damage not only to the person's apartment, but to three or four apartments around it in the same building. While they did fix the damage, they were not accommodating to the residents very well and it took forever to fix the apartments. A couple months later the same thing happens to an apartment facing my building. I decided to leave the complex after that. They do not care about the safety of their residents and will yank you every which way as you try to leave. THEN if you do leave they will try and say the reason you moved out was not fear for safety, but for other unrelated issues so they will not get in trouble. Horrible place to live. And that is just one thing, not to mention it takes them 4-5 days to fill out a maintenance request.

If I could give negative stars I would.

Can't speak to the quality of the pizza here as I have never partaken but as for the donairs I find them to be very tasty! The dissapointments one might find in ordering from here is that there are no extra veggie options. They offer lettuce,tomato,and onion whereas when I used to order from Buster's in Mill woods mall they had pickles,peppers,and black olives to name a few of the other choices. Also the wait times are a bit puzzling but I believe that is due to them concentrating more on getting their take out orders put out before dealing with the people in store (I actually waited 15 minutes for a donair once when there were no other people in the restaurant waiting ahead of me). I also believe there is some issues with being under staffed at this location as they have had the help wanted sign on their door now for quite some time. The staff are nice people though and they work with quite a bit of hustle in their step so I believe they are entitled to a little bit of patience when getting the food out.

PB&J flavored Nitro Cold Brew? Freakin' sold. 

Coffee shops around Florida take note. Ginger Beard Coffee has not one, not two, not three, BUT FOUR varieties of Nitro Cold Brew on tap! It's a win for local coffee shops to have one on tap, let alone four with niche flavors and tasting notes. 

I don't make proclamations like this often, however this was the best nitro cold brew I've had in recent memory. Hell, maybe all year!

From the moment we walked in, the lovely ginger-bearded man behind the counter treated us like royalty, in his own charismatic way. There were some hidden gems behind the counter that I can't necessarily comment on in a review. You'll have to find out for yourself. 

Next up, they have a wall of beers on tap. If it weren't for our post lunch coffee fuel up, I would have loved to really explored the beer they served in house. All in all, a wide open shop with tons of space for the coffee or beer aficionado. Must stop in Tampa!

We recently went to Tappers for a work event and it was a BLAST! I had been before they expanded into a new part of the building and it was fun but I enjoyed the new layout so much more. The pinball machines in the back work well and give a more open feeling near the bar rather than feeling like everything was squished in to a small space. We had such a good time and there were games for every taste. Some played video games - N64 is my jam! Some played more traditional arcade games - I was schooled in the art of Burger Time  And some even played fun board games and got a bit competitive over that connect four. The beers were great and I like that they have rotating taps. Also, I liked that they offer a small selection of cocktails as well - making sure there is something for every taste. I will for sure be back soon to keep practicing my Mario Kart skills.

I had a great manicure from Pat! She is so friendly and professional and the service was great. Definitely recommend calling ahead and making an appointment as they tend to get busy!! Well worth the price!

OK I'll admit it. This place .. WOW. Korean food is awesome but cupbop brings a whole new level to the experience. Be warned though getting your dish above a 7 rating in heat, you better have an iron gut.. for certain.

The customer service is excellent, and the employees here really care about their customers a great deal. Dont hesitate to try these guys out and follow their food truck too.. you wont be disappointed. But you will be satisfied.

I only had the iced coffee, but it was absolutely delicious and prepared fast. I also love that Volo is bicycle friendly - you will see lots of local riders here on the weekends after their rides. Top notch!
Great cleaning service.  These guys work very hard and stay until the job is done.  They are dependable and professional!

This restaurant was recommended to us by a local when we told them we wanted good seafood. It did not disappoint! Food was fast, tasty and a fun atmosphere! A good variety of options available. I had the shrimp Alfredo, my cousin had stuffed mahi and we split the add on crab legs. Highly recommend this place! Our server was Tim and was super helpful and friendly.

Sat in the drive-through for five minutes, no response. Drove around and had two employees sitting on the sidewalk smoking. Went into store, one employee at counter staring at customer with blankest strange expression for more than two minutes. Other employee taking order that seem to go on for eternity.
Opted to leave and go somewhere else because clearly food was going to be problematic. Hope their owner sees this.

Enjoyed Dinner. Suburb Service. Skip the Boar Chop.

Arrived in NO last evening and headed over to Brennan's for a steak. 
The filet was perfectly prepared, as always. Delicious. Got lured by the Boar Chop special ... after all, how often do you grill boar at home? It was ok. Thought it was a bit dry and the sauce was too sweet. The table next to us ordered burgers and fries ... those looked delicious as they went past.

Veggies were well prepared, just a bit al dente ... exactly how we like them.

The corn & crab bisque was boring. More corn chowder than anything. Thought it would benefit from a brandy/crime fraiche swirl on top. Perhaps some pepper/rosemary to liven it up. 

Son enjoyed the oysters and the gumbo.

Bread pudding was good. Lots of sauce which we proceed to dribble all over the table. Oops. 

The service, as always, was excellent. A team of 3 kept our water glasses full, fresh, warm bread with soft (not frozen) butter at the table, and were attentive. Should have posted this last evening, because now I've forgotten names... Jason, Rick (i think) and ?? .

I am going to start this review touching upon something mentioned in another post. Jess V stated "I really do appreciate the location of Distrito seeing as though I usually have to cross the bridge into Philadelphia for some good food." 

South Jersey is home to many great dining establishments, but no matter where you live, there is nothing like dining in the city because it provides an individual with so many options. Prior to my initial visit to Distrito I made the trip to Bueno Odena in Philadelphia for their tacos. I even made the trip one Saturday so that the wife could try their tacos. When the opportunity to dine at Distrito was finally afforded to me, my thought process mirrored Jess V's statement. 


The tacos at Distrito are prepared, presented, and taste very good. The tacos are packed... with delicious ingredients, and flavor. Every ingredient in the taco contributes to the fiesta of goodness mingling with my taste buds. The tacos, especially the fish tacos, are some of the best. No longer do I have to cross the bridge for good food...tacos at least. 
I know, I am going on and on about these tacos, but there are plenty of items that will satisfy your Mexican craving. Be it their skirt steak, ceviche, or fajitas, there are plenty of items on the menu. 


There is no bad time to dine at Distrito but Happy Hour, which is from 4-7 everyday is one of the best times. $5 Margaritas, $4 Beers, and $5 for two tacos, sounds like three hours of sheer happiness to me.

I decided to try someplace new to me on the way to a Lightening Game and I love tapas, so this is the place I chose.  What a find!

First, the ambiance.  The restaurant has a sleek, modern feel to it and appeared very clean and comfortable.  A solo guitarist playing Spanish-styled instrumentals set the mood ~ not too loud, not too quiet, just right.  I was there with a friend, but there were several couples and it would make a great place to have a date night.

We arrived around 6:30 pm and they have happy hour from 4-7 pm with $4 sangria and my friend had the red and I had the white.  They were both very good, so I would get there before 7 pm, if possible.  They had other happy hour specials too, but I can't remember what they were. 

Now the food...  We started with the "tapas tasting" off the entree menu to share.  We asked our server, Dillon, for some suggestions and it must have been kismet because he recommended three of the four things we had discussed when reviewing the menu on the way to the restaurant.  His recommendations were spot on.

We got the Pulpo a la Gallega, the Filete de Res and the Paella Valenciana.  The Pulpo a la Gallega was fantastic.  I love octopus when it is cooked correctly and can't stand it when it is not.  The octopus was cooked absolutely perfectly and the olive oil, garlic and paprika were ideally balanced to showcase the flavor rather than detract from it. The Filete de Res was also a perfectly balanced concoction of beef tenderloin, mushrooms and a sherry wine flambe.  Sublime!  The paella was also incredible with a good proportional mixture of ingredients. 

At this point, we were getting pretty full, so we just decided to order a couple more tapas and walk off our meal on the way to the game.  This time we got the Champiñones Extravaganza and the Empanadas de Carne.  The sauce on the mushrooms was absolutely sinful.  it was extremely rich and very filling, but we just couldn't tear ourselves away from the plate.  The empanadas were also superb, with a perfect beef mixture inside.

Overall, a splendid pick for a winning combination of service, atmosphere and marvelous food!

This is a very German food.  The beer is very nice in taste.  The lobby is large tables for dinner with strangers.  It's lively and there are good performances.  My husband and I like it very much.  I think they are more suitable for family gatherings because two people will be arranged in the corner, which makes us feel lonely and spends some time waiting to be found to order some food.

This should be negative stars
I had to move quick for house hunting. I would not recommend this to anyone.  After reading the other reviews (after the fact)
I will try to add photos later.
This is by far THE WORST Extended stay I have ever seen.
On the back side of the building the area near the stairs is filthy. No one has washed it down ever and the trash cans are right there so lots of evidence of spilling etc. gum removal stains all over the place. It is worse than a Wallly world parking lot.
Every day there are smokers sitting under the no smoking sign or smoking on the deck in front of doors next to non smoking rooms.

There here have been cigarette butts all over the place.  Many right around the trash cans where people smoke and staff does nothing about it.

Garbage in the parking lot and grounds. I have been here for three weeks. My wife is now in town and we will move to a different place.

The door doesn't fit the jam correctly and you can see outside from the inside near the bottom of door.
The doorway threshold looks as if it has never been cleaned..filthy!!
There is very little counter space in the bathroom
The shower curtain is mounted so high that it barely covers the edge of the tub.
There were bugs in it that I had to spray for.
The toilet was so brown in the bottom and under the rim that I told the house keeper about it.  Bless her hearts but she said that it wasn't my day. after my cleaning day came up all that was done was the linens were replaced.  She missed the dish towel.
The kitchen floor was not cleaned, like maybe ever!!!!. I was wondering why the shower got so dirty and I looked at my feet from being there barefoot(in the room only) so I took a wet paper towel to the floor and it was black. I bought some scrubbing bubbles and a cheap toilet brush and some cleanser. I had to clean the toilet and guess what...all the brown stains in the bottom of bowl are now gone. I have never in my life seen toilet in any hotel 3rd world included that was this bad.

Today (the 2nd day my wife has been here...some crackhead girl on a chopper bicycle with some sort of dinky gas motor...was yelling at someone in the morning there that they better pay her for what they got.

The shower/tub is small and it is stained with hard water deposits that are never cleaned. The floor wasn't cleaned. The bottom of the shower/tub floor is so warn that the fiberglass color is starting to show through.
Now come the fresh towels..Two were white and two were worn out dingy grayish white, I use better and cleaner rags to clean my Harley!!  I could have over looked the very old and dated kitchen b ut the filth and piss poor management of this place is unacceptable. I will be getting out this week.

They also have long term contracts with construction companies that have their employees that stay there comeing in drunk, smoking weed in the rooms and being very noisy. The staff does little.
Under know condition should the manager there be employed anywhere!!
Then comes the laundry room...the dryers are so worn that the finish is gone on the metal drums. Most worked..no matter what setting you had them on everything was high temp. Not very clean but that is par for this place.  Seriously this is the dirtiest franchise or non hotel I have seen in my life and I travel all over the world.



Front desk is slow to even get to the counter.

The pizza here is pretty good, although slightly overpriced in my opinion. The service has always been good and the location can't be beat if you're on the Bloomingdale neighborhood. I've ordered the calzone, pizza, chicken Parmesan, and garlic rolls. All were slightly lacking flavor, but were definitely better than some other places or even chains. I especially love the crispy dough typical of a New York style pizza.

This is my go-to Dim Sum spot in Tucson. There is a ton of variety in terms of dishes offered--lot's of dumplings, vegetables, and noodle dishes that really aren't offered elsewhere in Tucson. I am very fond of the fried shrimp balls, barbecue pork buns, and Chinese broccoli. The service here is really quick, even during peak Dim Sum hours on Sunday mornings I've never had trouble getting a table. Gee's is very accommodating to large groups, making it a nice Sunday brunch location.

May be the fault of smoothie place next door since this place doesn't serve food, but the entire place smells like a broken grease trap. Been in the industry for 20+ yrs and there is only one smell like that. Place is uninhabitable.
Mentioned it to the bartender and she said she couldn't smell it. Apparently she has worked there too long (like being blind to the fact that your house reeks of cat). This is beyond though, didn't know people could get used to anything including the smell of open sewage.
May or may not be their fault, but is their responsibility to deal with and fix it. Couldn't even bring myself to order a drink. Ouch!

I really wanted to like this place more than I actually did.  I'm torn between 3 and 4 stars.  This place is great for accommodating a large group.  We originally had 10 people and added 2 more at the last minute with no problem, on a Saturday night.  

The food  - this is the part that I wanted to like more.  I started off with the plantains. I love plantains and I like to try them everywhere I go.  These were....ok.....good, but not spectacular.  They were fried but not crispy and were covered in cheese, but it wasn't melted.  If you're looking for the best plantains, check out Dos Segundos.  Next I ordered an arepa with cheese and black beans.  I've had arepas in the past and this was not my favorite.  It was kind of dry and not very flavorful.  There wasn't enough cheese and the cheese that was on there wasn't melty enough.  They look small but they are deceptively filling, so I'm glad that's all I ordered.

The prices seem slightly high for the area and also for the food that you get.  I think the plantains were around $7 for a few small pieces.  

The service was great.  Very prompt and warm and friendly.  I sampled the desserts of my dining companions and they were outstanding.  This is where Sazon shines - hot chocolate and dessert.  It's BYOB too - always a plus. 

I will return but most likely just for desserts and chocolate.

Diane and CT I don't know you all personally yet, but you have outdone yourselves! My daughter and I just ordered a catfish platter with Mac and Cheese and extra cornbread on Door Dash. I am soooo glad I was able to support a local business. Everything was packaged so neatly down to the taper evident sticker and the sides in a different container so my catfish wasn't soggy! My catfish was flavorful and crispy! The Cheese pulls on the Mac and cheese made me soooo happy. My one year old ate catfish and her own slice of cornbread it was sooo good. We are local so we will be popping by this week to say hi and order more food! Thank you for an amazing experience. If your looking for amazing food please give them a try! You won't be disappointed

This place deserve no stars. Our group of friends tried to booked this Inn on June 7, 2020 night on booking.com, as we were traveling around Florida for our trip. We went to this place to check in and the lady ( I forgot her name) at the shift that night were awfully rude to us. We were getting to 2 rooms and as the lady was working on her computer for our checking in process, we asked the lady if we could get 2 rooms next to each other because we have 7 people and we are sharing shampoo and stuff and we also wanted to hang out so we don't want to rooms to be far from each other. She said "no", so after discussing with our friends we decided that we want to cancel and said sorry we don't want to get our room for that night. The lady started went off and cursing at us "get the f*** out of here". We were totally in shock!!! That this how a receptionist at a hotel or Inn treated us as a customer. Very unprofessional and rude. As shock as I were I asked her "this is how you treat your customer?" She said we're not customers and won't give us our receipt for our cancelation. Fine. Although we didn't book this place that night, but doesn't mean we wouldn't come back in the future because this Inn has a really good location, but this horrible receptionist just ruined our experience. Definitely never come back to this ghetto Inn.

I cannot say enough about this spot.  I know they will be successful through this pandemic because they have a huge outdoor seating area.     Fans at each table keeps the air moving, and hand sanitizer everywhere.    The employees make this place one of the most inviting spots in the city, with great music and flora and fauna to aid in the relaxation as you sip a glorious grapefruit hefewiezen.     Great Beer selection here to begin with.     You can get some giant brewskis in here in a giant cold beer mug.    OMG  great selection.  
Now I'm torn cause I've tried a bunch of things here.  My personal fave is schnitzel with hot german potato salad and cold.    The Nurnberger is a german styled reuben that is scrumptious as well.   They have a special as well that is a german styled pizza with bacon and onion that is heavenly.  They have great specials and even participate in the mardigras king cake ideal with pretzel as opposed to cake, and its killer.  You can get smallish snacks here, pretzels, and sausages on a stick.    The owner is always friendly and participates with his business associates and clientele.   Also participates in the various mardigras krewes, and art markets making the business accessible to the parade community, and community in general.   
The home of krampus, skinz n bonez, and krewe boheme. among a few.
If your looking for great food this is a nice change of pace for the city, german food is filling, very comfort oriented, and tasty.   Wash it all down with german beer.

Wie röstest du?

I love the burgers here, that may have to do a lot with the fact that I can have it made with the toppings I like. That being said, the meat and bun is very good. 

However they loose a star right off the bat because they now ask for a tip when you are ordering/paying at the counter... meaning this is counter service.  Me and my wife's bill is typically 40 bucks for 2 burgers 2 beers and 1 small fry. If you are not profiting enough from that to pay your employees well then you are doing something wrong. I have tipped here every time as far as I can remember, not 20 pct like I usually do because, again, it's counter service, but nothing I hate worse than asking for a tip before I've even had my food. Not that I have to tip at all but you make me look/feel like a jerk if I don't, thanks for that...

This is a new practice in the face of several new good burger joints that have popped up in the area. You just lost a long time customer. Super lame Burger Monger.

UPDATE... Always fresh, delicious, and did we say super friendly bunch behind the counter! FIVE STARS, yes!

Tremendous THAI FOOD, and yes it is gourmet!

Ever since they opened, their food is prepared with an excellent flare for the precise spices, seasonings and perfect selection of all the other very FRESH ingredients. As long as you do that. Let's eat! Shut the back door.

Please do not hesitate to enjoy to the max! Just in from the beach, no worries, this place is SBSC Santa Barbara Super-very-Casual and gets real busy at times... 

At the Empty Bowl they have the secret glue that keeps the place together some how. Lots of the restaurants, in the SBPM come and go, go, gonesville. Empty Restaurant cYaL8R... must be very challenging to operate in.

However with the Empty Bowl I say they have a giant anchor in their Big Bad Bowl holding down the center piece of eating extravaganzas, some are very popular and jam packed serving up just the right recipes!  (Hint see other Yelp Reviews)

At times the wonderful Taco Team guys next door (Corazon Cocina) are packing them in, You don't have to wait, you can quickly grab an empty seat at the Empty Bowl counter, and at times they will get you started straight away. The counter will be empty in one minute and the next it is jammed and buzzing with happy eaters and maybe a few noodlers as well. 

Recently we were a party of four at the Empty Bowl, three orders were perfect, one order was to be all veggie and they accidentally snuck in some natural free range, gourmet, slow roasted, lovely tasting well seasoned chicken. Oops, they quickly made it right for my buddy  and he stated is was perfect. No cluck for that buck! They were very apologetic for the menu order mixup.

Do enjoy! Excellent take away as well.

Hot tip, FREE PARKING underground, enter from Chapala!

God we love this place, never enough. ;~} again really enjoy...

Right off Hwy 23, .1 mile down on right, across from the plaquemine sheriff's office.  My husband and I ordered a foot long shrimp poboy and split it.  It was fully dressed and the bun was fresh and delicious.  The shrimp were fried and delicious.  One if the best shrimp poboys I've ever had.  Worth the effort finding it but don't forget to bring your cash b/c they only accept cash.
Great vegan option- just eggs. Not sure if it's an every weekend item but such a good spot for veggies and non veg people!

Parking was easy (street), and the place was large and airy. What you'd expect from a newer Starbucks. We entered and immediately felt the positive energy from the staff. Friendliest most welcoming Starbucks staff I've ever come across.  Thank you for making our Sunday morning brighter.

It's interesting to see why places like Starbucks are so successful--much to my dismay. It is because abhorrent service and poor product consistency from places like green line cafe. I'm curious if it feels good to the employees to make everyone who walks in feel like the dirt beneath their feet? Or if they take pride in consistently offering poor quality products due to either completely altered mental status or general apathy. Either is unacceptable for an employee at McDonald's where one is likely to receive better customer service than I did here. 

I ordered two iced coffees with a splash of coconut. I received two iced coffees that were one fourth coconut and so sweet that I physically could not swallow the product. It was pure syrup. My assumption is that the barista didn't know what a splash meant, which is unfortunate for him. But what was more unfortunate was the disgusting display of disdain and attitude he displayed when asked to remake the drink. Peace out green Lane, lucky for me hub bub has better service, better product, and is only a few extra blocks away.

All they want to do is up sell, they do not care about your time or money. They just want you to schedule and get you there to feel awkward. I book my appointment on 10/16 they did not have anyone available on the weekends which is odd. So I booked for the following week, Monday 10/19 they were already calling to reschedule. The fact the are not able to book your appointment correct should have been a sign. Next I specify told her on 10/16 I only want my forehead done for the deal of $189. Never once did she tell me there is a possibility if you do not do your frown lines you have a 50% change of forehead dropping. That is pretty huge. So I took time off work drove 1 hour with traffic to get there. I waited at the door the receptionist had her back turned and on her phone the women who was administering the Botox on her phone no one paying attention. Then I got taken back and that is when they turned the sales game on, also making me feel awkward about not wanting to drop $1000 on generic brand Botox for my husband and I. The thing that pissed me off was no communication if I had known I could not get just my forehead done I wouldn't have wasted my time. 

BEWARE IS AL I CAN SAY.
My husband accidentally ordered the wrong meal and they were very accommodating in rushing his new meal. Great customer service.

I go in that was my  first mistake.. I normally go to one location when I do eat their chicken and it is not often, but being lazy, didn't want to drive across town but since I was already in the area!  I wanted a 11 piece 2 breast 2 legs 7 wings.. WELL,  sorry was told We can't do that.. (Even with upcharge) NO we can't!  OK...

Ok, what can you do? We can do 2 breasts 4 thighs 2 legs 3 wings. Well, I don't eat thighs! The girl behind the counters tells me  I can give you 2 breasts, 5 wings, 4 legs,  I get home,  I have 2 breasts, 3 wings and 6 legs and  highly disappointed because the coating on the chicken taste as if it was cooked over and over again in old grease almost like a burnt taste. NEVER going back here again!  lesson learned  When you get a hard time.. and you are willing to pay extra and you still get a hard time LEAVE!

I have been to around ten different retros throughout NJ and eastern Pa and this is easily the best of the bunch. Tons of equipment and cardio, very friendly staff and immaculate on the floor and in the locker room. They care about the business and it shows.... other Retros should learn from their example.

I had a great experience with Quality Moving Experts. Scheduling my move was easy and the office staff was very courteous. Movers arrived close to 8 AM as promised and got right to work. They moved some very heavy furniture pieces out of the house and was able to deliver it to my friends house several miles away. The movers were very punctual and very efficient with boxing up and moving things out of the residence, without damaging any of the walls or furniture itself.

Furthermore, it saved me an immense amount of time from having to takeoff work. They were extremely flexible with working with me and my budget, not to mention the crew was very friendly and professional in knowing exactly what to do and how to do it. They mayNot have been the lowest price but they sure were thorough aNF maintained open communication through the whole process.  

Their quote was less than half of what similar companies were quoting at the time. Not to mention with their interface it was easy to add to the inventory and info online! 

Would definitely recommend with the highest regard!

I am happy and sad with this visit to Vashti. Unfortunately, this store is permanently closed effective 05/26/2018. After hearing about this Trinidadian cuisine I finally had the chance visit and sadly I happened to visit on the last day of business. The restaurant is island style with family members working together to service patrons. The food was piping hot and tasted very good. 
I had a doubles with slight pepper = crispy bara (shell) and the channa was well seasoned and tasted great (garbanzo beans). I also had the goat roti - very good. Sad to see this business go.
Pleasant atmosphere, filling and very satisfying meal and incredibly warm and friendly staff! I would highly recommend and will be back there many more times

The young Mexican girls here are lazy and act like they dont want to be there, and heaven forbid that you might want a cup of coffee.
The portions are small and the young girls are rude.
Pass on this one

Highly recommend if you're looking for a good cafe in the area! This is absolutely one of my new favorite cafes in Philadelphia. The food is phenomenal. 

During my visit, I had a small espresso with whipped cream...which made me ask myself why have I never added that before?! It was so tasty and hit the spot. I also stuffed my face with the sicilian style eggs, pisa panini,  a breakfast cannoli, the quattro formaggi crepe, and gelato. Everything was outstanding! I definitely ate my weight in food, but it was totally worth it and I'm really looking forward to my next visit. The owner and his staff are so friendly and are great with giving recommendations. They also make you feel like you're in Italy which was probably one of my favorite things about my visit here.

Very cool concept, just what the Reno/Sparks area needs. I was able to pick up some ice cream, awesome Ahi Poke, locally made soaps, and a metal cutout of Tahoe all within 10 minutes. Where else in the city can you do that? I had a blast walking around and supporting the local businesses. Will definitely be back soon!

I've been having shoes repaired at this place for over 20 years they were in another location close to the different entrance... there have been several issues, however acceptable somewhat until - Saturday was the last time I will do business, I picked up my shoes had the wrong soles installed even though we talked about it and made it clear they would not do anything except take couple dollars off. Horrible horrible way to do business, I'm done - period.

The North Star Bar was a really interesting experience. To be fair, I went to see Uh-Huh-Her there and the place was covered in lesbians, so we may not have been the regular clientele. I really liked the room that the concert was actually in--it was spacious and really nice for shows. The back bar was a good addition too. I also appreciated the beer list, which was extensive.

I did not like that everyone has to wait in the much smaller main bar before the show and that the show started incredibly late (apparently this is a chronic condition for the North Star). So....I think it'd be fun to hang out it, but I'm not sure that I'll go to another show there.

This place was good, but not great. We came right before the rush, which was helpful, though found service to be still a bit slow.

Definitely go with the chargrilled oysters! Skip the boo fries. The cajun sampler was a nice choice of everything, but I didn't find it all that tasty. The spicy shrimp/oyster po boy, on the other hand, was delicious and splitting it with someone turned out to be a great idea.

In Acme's defense, we probably should have completely focused on seafood and not diverted to regular cajun fare.

This is my 2nd time staying at this hotel, and while I do love it the only thing that isn't good? Don't stay on the 4th floor. It is a pet-approved floor and both times there has been a little yappy dog barking - ugh! Here right now and I'm hoping the dog barking this time doesn't do it late at night, middle of the night or early morning. 
First time I stayed here and there was a dog yapping early in the morning (could even hear it over the sound machine!) I called the front desk and all they said was something to the effect of "I think they're checking out soon" but it wasn't the first occurrence.  
I have pets that are my family & that I love dearly, but owners need to be held more responsible for their pets behaviors/noise here.
Aside from this happening twice - months apart - the hotels atmosphere, staff, drinks and food are GREAT! Love, love, Love the themed suites too!

Found this place on Yelp with great reviews so decided to check it out. Not disappointed. Found a great, close spot with the food you know but with a different kick to it. Buffalo chicken cheesesteak and three cheese quesadillas were great. The staff was super friendly and the place was super clean. Can't wait to try the wings!

My husband wants to give this 6 stars. We came here two days in a row after our first visit. The shrimp tacos are delicious. My husband had the carnitas torta and raved about how insane it tasted. Keep up the good food Seis.
The bar tender was THE WORST. how could someone in "customer service" be so rude?! I honestly wouldn't go back just because of him.

Visited the WW2 Museum and their restaurant had a 40 minute wait.  We looked for something close that was reasonably priced and found Ugly dog.  Had the chicken wings, bbq sandwich, bbq pork with mac and cheese, and cheeseburger.

Great tasting with tender meat.

Only knock was that it took about 20 minutes to get the food.

One of the few pleasant surprises in New Orleans.

Recommend it.

Dr. Matt and his staff have been nothing but helpful and exemplary in service. When starting their I had issues with range of movement shoulders neck back and even knees and hands. Since I've been going my range of movement has improved tremendously and I'm no longer sore just sitting while working. The therapy on my knee has made it to the point where light exercise and walking is back on the table.

Tonight was my first time here, and I had a great experience. The burger was very tasty, and the fries were perfectly crispy. To top off the food, Juan helped us with our order, and he was very helpful and pleasant. He even came by our table during the meal to make sure we were enjoying ourselves. Juan was very personable with us, and he made our experience tonight extra special. We will certainly be back again soon!

We went through the drove thru and the woman taking the order kept laughing and when we were done ordering she didn't tell us anything and we just assumed she got it. She didn't, she got the donuts wrong, she gave us a chocolate muffin instead of a blueberry muffin and completely forgot to put a frozen lemonade in the order even though we heard her repeat it back to us. It was the worst experience I've ever had at a Dunkin' Donuts.

I'm not sure how people can NOT like the Flying Saucer. There are maybe the best hot pretzels I've ever had, dipping sauces, seats aplenty, booze, and a long-term beer drinking contest.

This outpost is right next to a sumptuous train station-turned-hotel that is definitely worth a look. There was plenty of seating even though football playoffs were on (the projection screen isn't the sharpest, guys), and our knowledgeable waitress helped me find an absolutely delicious strawberry beer that I had never heard of.

Loved it.

I really love that when you ask for good beer and mussels in the city, there are more than a few options. These reasons drove me to the Belgian Cafe one night last week. I've been here before, but only for drinks. I really like this spot, because it has outdoor seating, a nice bar, an open area if it gets crowded, and a nice seating area. Inside and out, it looks better than your average everyday restaurant. While atmosphere doesn't seem to add a lot, it's nice to sit in a comfortable area. Throughout the meal, our server seemed to leave us without beer for longer than I would have liked, but this is my only complaint. He was really knowledgeable about beer, and that makes up any small error in serving.

Looking at the beer list and menu, it's no surprise that this restaurant is a Tom Peters venture. The beer list is excellent, with a couple of Belgians on tap at $7 a glass, and a great selection from around the rest of the world and country. A taplist is available online, and although it's slightly outdated because they change beer quickly, it still can give you a good idea. I stayed domestic for the night with the Avery White Rascal (I'm really into Avery lately) and the Anchor Liberty Ale. I was dining with Rachel for the evening, and she was enjoying the Duchesse De Bourgogne. If you can't find something on tap you like, you're: A) likely crazy, and B) not going to be let down by the bottle list. Beer is easily the forte of the whole establishment (as it should be).

The menu leaves something to be desired. To be clear, the menu is not bad. But it seems like the exact same thing as Monk's, and if that's what I wanted, I would just go there. The Belgian Cafe serves up burgers, mussels, and larger entree dishes. After deliberation, we ordered a large pot of mussels in a sauce of of jalapeno pepper butter, cilantro, orange zest, and belgian wit ale. They were solid, and good, but not amazing. Still, it's a really nice dish to share, and comes with a (obligatory) order of tasty fries.

Bottom Line: It seems that my standards are getting too high. Where I would normally rave about this spot, I'm now inclined to tell you to walk up the block if you're in fairmount, or tell you to hit up Monk's if your craving the best Belgian spot around. Don't get me wrong, this is a good solid eatery. I think I'd just rather hit it up in passing as opposed to making it the main event for the evening. And if every spot seems to be crowded in the neighborhood, the Belgian Cafe still has room for you and your friends.

I love the new Hot Room Fishers location! I signed up right before the pandemic and statewide shutdown hit and after waiting months for businesses to open back up, I was hesitant at first on whether I should cancel my membership. They encouraged me to come by and take a class to see the precautionary measures they put in place. After taking my first class there, I was more than pleased at their intentional social distancing measures. The class size was considerably smaller to what I'm used to pre-covid. I appreciate how they place markers so you know you have enough space between you and the next person. The facility itself is sparkling clean. There wasn't ever a point during my experience from start to finish where I felt like social distancing was an issue. Everyone was considerate of each other and efficient in entering and exiting. The staff are incredible and truly want to encourage you to be your best self, which is why I find myself back here to practice. NO ONE judges you for what you can or cannot do. They always remind you to do the best you can even if that means modifying some of your poses. I'm so happy The Hot Room finally joined the Fishers community!

I wonder if the short girl who looks like a generic Gaga still works there. She was a rude little beast of a thing. I shop at Citrus Park's Sephora now and all their associates laugh because when I tell them how horrible the customer service is at International Mall, they already know. They tell me, "you don't know how many come here and complain to us about International Mall's Sephora employees."
When you call down to the front desk to ask what premium channels I get in my room and they say Showtime but told me to search the channels to find it.  Lack of customer service.

Outstanding work!  The whole crew was clean cut, polite, efficient and skilled.  My new roof really upgraded the appearance of my home, so I was very pleased.  Gutters look and work great as well.  I would absolutely recommend them!

Probably one of the worst first impressions I've had of a local business NE Tavern has the potential to be a chill little neighborhood pub but from my first (and last) visit to the joint all I can say is mediocre service, mediocre food and the end of the evening was met with the rudest owner I've ever encountered who made it quite clear that our choice to come here and and spend cash in this place on a Tuesday night was a complete mistake. Save your time there are tons of other independent businesses in this city that actually appreciate their customers!
Only place my Dax will get a hoagie!  Love their food also..  it's been a go to for many many years

I typically am never too excited about more high end Asian restaurants, I tend to find that mom and pop restaurants and smaller locations have better, more authentic food, but for what Thai Prime is offering I was not disappointed at all.

Green curry is my litmus test for Thai food and I have to say, there wasn't anything disappointing about the green curry with chicken. I ordered it hot spicy (I'm pregnant so I'm more sensitive to spicy food right now but I'll update in a couple months when I can go back and test out their Thai spicy) and it was honestly the perfect amount of spicy, even without being pregnant. It made my nose run, but I could still taste all of the complexity in the flavors.

A friend and I went this past Friday after work, and the only two complaints I have are the fact that my food was put on the table nearly five minutes before hers and the parking lot for the plaza is pretty hairy if you don't get there at a decent time. 

Overall, I would recommend Thai Prime and will definitely go back to try their other options.

5 stars for the sushi. 4 stars for the Pad Thai. 

I went to this restaurant twice and both times it was a very nice experience. The atmosphere is incredible! The service was very nice. The miso soup and sushi were both fantastic! 

Why 4 stars instead of 5? There's two reasons actually. The Pad Thai was talked up so much the first time we went but it ended up being rather mediocre when we came back to try it. Then, the second time we went, we asked for recommendations, the server didn't seem to know the menu super well and ended up making me doubt whether anything was good due to her personal dislike of most things I mentioned on the menu. I've never heard a server answer like that when asked for recommendations.

All I can say is you can never go wrong with portillos!   Even the chocolate cake is amazing. If you ever come in the summer you have to try the lemon cake shake ! It is amazing, they do not offer the cake during the winter . My go to is the big beef with hot amd sweet peppers.  Can never go wrong , even if you dont like hot peppers try the sweet . Glad they came to the city

Absolutely amazing!!!!! Lena was our tour guide and she was phenomenal! We started the tour at the VooDoo Lounge (where you can get 2 for 1 hurricanes if going on a tour) then walked approx 4 blocks to the cemetery. We made plenty of stops on the way where she explained much of the city's history. Once arriving at the cementary it is very crucial to stay with your group, as it is prohibited to enter the cementary without a guide. We were able to see many above ground tombs,including some of the most famous,and learn all about them as well as the burial process. Personally feel this is a must when visiting NOLA. Lena was very informative and professional! 

Side note: we were there July 26-29. It was HOT HOT HOT!!!! Dress cool, take waters with you (can also purchase during tour), our guide let us borrow extra mini umbrellas to get some shade but you may want to take your own.

Simply not good.  As ok as ok gets.

The employees here were very pleasant.

They cannot do orders over the phone for whatever reason- only through the app.

The food itself was not worth the price.  Tons if better options nearby.  No seasonings!
Awesome service!! Cold beer!!! We are  from Louisa KY I will surely stop every time I'm this way. Great bartender

This is one of the largest Billiard halls in Nashville and also the least relaxing.  They have plenty of tables to choose from, and their the full sized pay by the hour kind so its the real deal here.  Everything else is pretty much mediocre.  They have a full bar, but they're drinks, like everything else on 2nd avenue are pretty expensive.  There is a relaxed atmosphere which is refreshing from the madness that can happen on 2nd Avenue, especially on the weekends.  The best time to go is before seven during the week when the tables are free.  They have a few drink specials but nothing really special.  

The worst thing about this place is it's location.  2nd Avenue is incredibly congested, it's really hard to find parking to get here and when you do find some its usually very expensive.  There are a lot of different places to walk to if you decide to do something other than play pool or shoot darts, but expect to spend your time dodging crowds.

Very bad. Felt & looked unclean. I only gave 1 star because I couldn't give zero. 

The key to our room didn't work. 
2nd key didn't work either. 
3rd try, they gave us a different room. That room was dirty and the bed wasn't made. 
4th try, key didn't work. They sent maintenance up for a 5th try and he couldn't get the key to work either. Then he realized that someone was already occupying that room!  
THEY HAD GIVEN ME THE KEY TO AN OCCUPIED ROOM!

I wondered how I could get a good night's sleep knowing that they may give away a key to my occupied room!!!

The front desk was very friendly but I can't see calling them anything other than incompetent. 

We left and went to the Marriott. Much, much cleaner, quicker and free parking.   

Clarion tried to process a credit but after 20 minutes, they said it's ok to leave; they'd call in 10 minutes to confirm the credit. That was an hour ago. Now I have to call them to make sure I get credited. 

Or, do you think I should trust them?

We had a great experience with Enterprise.  We rented an 8 passenger mini van for a week.  When we got there to pick it up, they gave us a choice of a new Pacifica or a Kia.  We fell in love with the Pacifica!  Jennifer did a FANTASTIC job for us in the Avon location!  I highly recommend her!  Also, the rep who took us out to the vehicle was outstanding in customer service!  There was just a little bit of cleaning fluid in the dash area, and he didn't  want to let us go until he cleaned it up.  (We didn't let him, it was fine and it definitely showed that they had  the Pacifica sparkling clean for us, inside and out!) great experience, highly highly recommend!!

We order out every Friday while visiting my Grandfather in South Philly. We decided to try this place and they didn't disappoint. My Grandfather gave the Kosmo Burger 10 on a scale of 1-10. My husband and I split a cheese steak. It was amazing. Full of meat. No skimping. We also had a pizza (kids loved it), fries (crispy just like we like them) & onion rings (once again no skimping,  healthy portion.)  Not to mention that the prices are reasonable. We will definitely be making more trips back.  Can't wait to try their salads!

Nice escape at night to sit back, have a drink and an appetizer and enjoy very good music. One too though is you're there to listen to the music, do not let them site you to the right of the stage. That section is set far enough so the music is muffled.

Was in the Wilmington area for a couple weeks for business. This place stood out from all others...It was awesome. Salad based on shredded brussel sprouts, spicy linguini pasta, really good honey wheat bread with cheese. I tried the duck which was a long shot for me, and it was good but not great (just me). Good drinks and nice, small venue. Very impressed.

I love cookies. I usually bake my own ... I am judgy. Crumbl is okay. Some creativity with flavors. Not much variety in texture. Most of the flavors are simply relying on sweetness. $12 for 4 cookies of this caliber is just never going to happen again. Service was good and they have nice energy. Pura Vida

First time I have dined in at a restaurant in 3 months. The tables have plenty of distance and staff all wore masks. That's the best I can say. Service was slow, no follow up by waitress so certainly the 'bottomless' soda and fries didn't happen. All of our fries were cold in delivery, almost done eating when warm fries arrived. Brownie in the brownie sundae was stale and hard.  Too many great burger places around to have to put up with this.

Organized a reservation for my climbing team while we were here for a competition. It was a great bonding experience and beautiful space. Our reservation ended at 6pm and we all had plans to eat at The Eddy. They unfortunately sprung a last minute "policy rule" and denied our party. Reno Axe had the space and was kind enough to accommodate our team. Thank you so much Reno Axe!!
I can't think of a reason why really GOOD service annoys me. Too much of a good thing I guess. Food was pretty good but overpriced. The service was excellent but overboard.

Wow i haven't been to this place ina while, but I love it!  It has a very nostalgic atmosphere and takes you back to old Ybor.  Dinner is massive and you get a lot for what you pay.  I remember my fav part of the meal is the Spumonti at the end - deEEeeeEElish!

This is my favorite brunch place in Philly. 

1. it is fun to look at... i like the decor and there is usually some fun art on the walls.

2.  CANOLI FRENCH TOAST.

3. the homemade hot sauce oh my god. 

these are really enough for me... I might also suggest the wild mushroom frittatta because it is fantastic, as is the breakfast burrito (extra hot sauce on the side please!!!!).  They also have Limonciatta, which isn't rare, but makes me smile.  

I am very unhappy that the pumpkin canoli french toast was something i missed and would like it very much if it came back before summer......
Nice middle eastern market on Busch Blvd. excellent customer service and has everything you're looking for to fill up your middle eastern kitchen! God bless!

Cute little coffee stall at the market. I typically go for a mocha, but wanted to try something different. Had a Perfect 10; steamed milk, espresso, honey, and cinnamon. Super tasty, not too much honey and the cinnamon blended in well. Staff is nice and friendly. They make it to order and I believe they pull the espresso shots individually.

Truly an amazing dinner experience, and I am so glad that we were able to make this stop during our time in New Orleans. The staff was incredibly attentive, and the service and recommendations they provided during our dinner were fantastic. Not only was the food spot on, but so were the cocktails we selected. 

During our dinner there, we ordered the seafood platter, hushpuppies, and fish sticks. We also ordered the whole grilled fish as our entree to share among six people. The seafood was overall incredibly fresh, and everything was prepared very well. Everything was generously seasoned, and incredibly flavorful without being too overbearing. 

During our next visit to NOLA, we will 110% be sure to return!

A great tradition after a long day at the beach.  Also fun if you happen to just be driving by.  I don't know what they do to their ice cream to make it so light and creamy, but it's absolutely delicious.

I liked the location, but the pizza and the service was awful. The dough was undercooked and grainy, leaving a bad taste in my mouth. As did the cheese; it tasted like plastic and slid right off the entire slice in one bite. Not only did I have to wait around 40 minutes to get my pizza, but I had to sit, watching all customers who came after me, get their pizzas first. The service felt dismissive and rude, not attentive at all, creating a tense and unenjoyable environment.

Amazing: bacon melt, brisket sliders, Mac n cheese

100% of all people should go here. Don't fugghh around and miss out on this legit food mouth situation, you peasant.

The service here was phenomenal.  Either the previous reviewers were just bratty or the management took what they had said to heart, which means even more in my book. Service was extremely attentive.  Water class was always full.  The server would constantly keep up updated on our food status without us even asking.  Perhaps their meals take longer than average because they use fresh ingredients because their dishes do taste very fresh.  The calamari would be a solid starter, as well was the wedding soup.  Soup was a bit expensive for its size, but it was still delicious.  The seafood appetizer (mussels and clams) were great.   All shells were open and all the meat was there.   I got the sword fish which was cooked to perfection and came with a generous steamed broccoli stalk that had that perfect crisp.   My boyfriend had a pasta dish that was also very good called the Pappardelle ai Funghi e Mascarpone.   I really do highly recommend this place regardless the previous negative reviews.  Even if those reviews were true to an extent, the restaurant took it as constructive criticism and made a change.  Give them a chance.

P.S.  When I ordered the soup, the waiter brought out an extra spoon "I case I decided to be nice and share" which I thought to be very thoughtful.

Outback has always been a 'Plan B' place for us when 'Plan A' doesn't work. We prefer sit at the bar to avoid long waiting time and most guests at the bar are likely minding their own business but don't mind crank few jokes with you. Bartenders are all very friendly and services are prompt.

There are not too many surprise on the menu. Everything is average taste but they do try to be creative and majority customers are happy of what they've get. Happy hour is definitely worth the money for both beer and house wine. They are currently serve tapas at the bar. We tried few dishes and liked l lot. Good portion for bar food not mention reasonable price. If you need a light dinner, it is not a bad approach. 

Indeed it is a chain restaurant. However, give the energetic atmosphere  and customer first service, it will always be my back up plan that is simple, safe and predictable.

I wanted to review our 3-night stay over Thanksgiving. First...this is a "pet friendly" hotel and apparently one of the few in the area so there were a lot of dogs. I have no issues with dogs, however, I do with them inside the pool area where you may doze off at the pool and they start barking. OR at the breakfast tables while you're trying to eat as dogs are staring, whining and barking at you. Those two areas should be off limits! Housekeeping does a great job of cleaning but if you have allergies, you may have a reaction. 
The hotel is on a busy road. It is loud. I could not hear anything from inside our but the road runs next to the pool. And while they did their best with a large water feature to drown out the noise, the road is louder and then add the barking dogs were the added noise. So not a relaxing feel at the pool. 
The hotel is near every restaurant and store you may need. The kitchen in the room is perfect for having cold foods or snacks on hands, or microwave some popcorn, without having to run out all the time. 
I would not stay at the location again due to the pets, but if you don't mind or are traveling with your pet, the place would be good for you.

The atmosphere is amazing. Great spot for happy hour, date night, or Sunday brunch! The food is so great- good portion sizes, creative, and just so yummy. Danna the owner came over and greeted us, she is lovely. I had champagne and the Caesar, both delicious and our bar tender was so courteous and attentive! Not disappointed!

This place was absolutely disgusting. We went there yesterday and found expired meats and meat that was green and brown. There was a guy walking by us that had a shopping cart full of trash and while he was walking by the fresh meat case he started arranging the packages of meat. How nasty!! On top of all this there was pork and chicken in their packages that were bloated and full of air. What's worse is that I'm sure they will use all this meat to make ground beef. I plan on reporting them.

First time in town and we loved the vibe of this breakfast spot. Service was good, loved the music selection. 
I had the belt sandwich and mint lemonade. Delicious!!! It was fresh ingredients and perfectly toasted. The lemonade was house made as well.

The one downside was the biscuits and gravy. Very bland and the biscuits were hard. My husband ended up eating off my plate. 

Win some, lose some but we would definitely come back.

I live right by Hokkaido so I was totally excited to see a sushi/thai place open near my house!! I always want Pad Thai and one sushi roll so this place is perfect for that!  I was skeptical at first about how good the sushi would be, but I am definitely a fan and have loved everything I have ordered so far!  The prices are really reasonable and recently they have been doing a 15% off deal so everything is super cheap!  Also, last time I was in there picking up an order (two days ago) everyone sitting at the bar had these awesome looking drinks so I plan on trying whatever that was next time I dine in at the restaurant.  

I would definitely recommend this place to friends in the city and I will be ordering from here a lot! Actually, I think I will order from here tonight :)

Pretty unique dirty hipster place.  I enjoyed a visit but dont necessarily need to go back.

The standards were here.  Cool music, weird crowd, cheap beers and crappy bathrooms.
Great atmosphere, great barber (Don B) was great cleaned me up nice ...definitely recommend this place

Receptionists are very hostile, and no effort is made to make the customer experience pleasant. More coaching is needed at this location on how to treat people with courtesy and care. It was my first time there, I walked out, and I'm never going back.

Noise noise everywhere. When we checked in the pool was literally swimming with children..... When we got to the room there was all sorts of music playing on the beach and there were a ton of people everywhere. We left and came back around 9:30 pm and there wasn't a parking spot to be found. All I wanted to do was go to the hot tub..... we drove around aimlessly for 20 minutes and finally went in to ask where we 
Could park. The front desk staff indicated we needed to park across the street behind the Walgreen's. There were chains across the entrance of the parking lot and we couldn't get in. After a few minutes we got out and moved the chain aside. After parking, to get to our room, we had to cross 6 major lanes of traffic in order to get back to the property. 

We got to the room and I called down to ask if I could use the hot tub. The front desk lady said no..... because It would disturb other guests and there was a concern about noise. Well, it was 10:45 pm at this point and there was a stereo going full blast in the pool area. I don't understand how I, as one single 
Person sitting in the hot tub would be able to make as much noise as the stereo was making but whatever. This was supposed to be a vacation and instead has turned into a struggle that we are paying over 200.00 a night for.  

Overall this place was a super big bummer.

We went there on Friday afternoon, drove less then 2 hrs from queens, NY, arrived a little after 1pm, staff were pretty friendly(except the kitchen staff, felt like 20 some yrs ago back in school cafeteria...), if you can, bring your own food or just swing to pats or genos cheese steak.... you can reenter within the day with your ticket.
The play materials were suitable for kids from about 2.5 yrs to 6 yrs old...beyond that.. I think a science museum would be a better bet, such as the liberty science center in NJ. But my son is about 2.5 yrs old, he had a lot of fun, loved the automotive area and the water table area, could not drag him away. lower level area is a little dim for me, and it certainly has room for improvement, such as an area for locomotives and airplanes... we stayed until 5pm (close time). make a trip there with your young ones, time and money well spent...you'll light up too when u see them having so much fun!!!

Excellent food, less than stellar service. There's no question the food here is delicious, I was nothing but happy with the items I ordered. Though on both occasions that I started my day at this bakery, the server (the same woman both days, with pink hair) treated me like an incompetent idiot. I can understand a one-off bad day, or if the questions I'd asked her had been particularly dumb, but both times my questions were harmless. On the first day, I asked what was in the chickpea salad, because it looked delicious. She rolled her eyes and said 'It's chickpeas.', as if I wasn't asking for an expansion of what was written on the label. The second time I went, I ordered a latte and paid with a card. She was obviously very busy and I got the (perhaps false) impression that she had forgotten to return my card. When she passed me the latte and I asked, just to be sure, 'Sorry, can I just get my card back?' she once again looked at me with disdain and in a condescending tone said 'Yeah, of course, I'm doing that right now.' I don't know if I caught this woman on two particularly off days or if she always treats the customers this way, but it is certainly not how I want to start my mornings off. I've never written a Yelp review before, but I was so upset and thrown off by being treated this way, and I hope given the quality of Bywater Bakery's food, that they come to improve the quality of their service as well.

If your looking for something satisfying and healthy after all the beignets, gumbo and chargrilled oysters, this is the spot! We came here two mornings in a row , It was never crowded and the turkey/fog/goat cheese crepe was amazing! My fiancé got a chia seed hemp bowl & the prosciutto crepe, he loved them both as well

I loved visiting this place and the owner, Jay, was charming and hospitable. I came back another day to get one more item and was warmly greeted and welcomed in as a friend. Can not recommend enough! Check them out when you are in town for a unique experience.

Loved the Decor such a lovely place fun lots to look at. Food was really good I had the smoked salmon eggs Benedict and a slice of cappuccino cream pie -- they have outside dining on nice days --fun place ,, great atmosphere , good food

Delicious little food truck! Got the opener on wheat which was fantastic! Definitely
Recommend this place!!!

Have been a couple of times. food is fairly good, prices can vary depending on what items you get, mostly paying for the views and your beautiful mountains, nice to try though especially if you are here visitng.

The food was really delicious! I ordered the fish and chips and my husband had the chicken pesto pizza. All super tasty except for the coleslaw... it's supposed to be Chipotle/spicy coleslaw but it just doesn't taste very good. I also ordered a side of their mac and cheese which is SO GOOD but pretty heavy for a main course. 

A couple problems: when my husband asked for a beer recommendation, the waitress admitted she wasn't great at pairing but recommended the Sinistor Black. A dark, chocolate-noted beer with a pesto pizza? Um no. Into pairings or not, that was way off. He ended up picking and IPA that was more what he was looking for. Overall, our waitress was ok but when it came time to pay, it took 15 minutes for her to come get our payment. Not horrible but I am 8 months pregnant, it was getting hotter (sitting outside), and those seats started to get very uncomfortable.

Despite a few disappointments with our waitress, we really love 10 Barrel! The food is great and the beer is great too!
Fast and friendly service. Impressed on how considerate they were to food allergies and the extra precautions they took regarding such. Food was delicious! Will come back.

All of these positive reviews surely aren't lying. Hawthorne's is a phenomenal brunch place located just far enough from South Street that you forgot you're so close.

We got there before 10am on a Saturday and only had to wait about 10 minutes. I can imagine the wait only increases from there.

My boyfriend ordered the Crabby Dick, which is 100% a must-try. The amount of crab you get is incredibly generous - the whole dish is phenomenal. 

I was going to order the Huevos Ahogados, but our wonderful server offered some advice that led me to opt for the Hawthorne's Omelet instead. The filling of the omelet (braised short rib, caramelized onion, sharp cheddar) is an unusual omelet combination, but one I will remember for a long time. The short rib was tender, juicy, and had a ton of flavor. I was thrilled with my omelet, but the Crabby Dick won me over and I will get that next time.

I loved the crispy homefries, BF didn't care for them as much. 

Service was great! Our server was really friendly, helpful, and attentive. As mentioned earlier, she answered some questions about the Huevos Ahogados and persuaded me to try the omelet instead - a recommendation I was very thankful for.

I frequent El Vez any chance I get mostly for lunch or for drinks. The lunch specials are a great price and an abundance of food. The guacamole is the best in the city along with the margaritas. Service is always on point. I recommend to everyone that inquires on where to dine in the area.
