Got the chicken and beef chimichangas and an order of the endless enchiladas. Salsa has a nice kick. Our server Kayla was excellent.
Good juices but SLOW! Every time I have gone, I've had to wait forever for my juice and it's not cheap!

The honeymoon is definitely over for me here.  I'm looking for another gym.  If you are thinking about joining here, please consider the following:

1.  Despite the high def TV setup with 20 TVs, they will not under any circumstances change the TV channel for you.  For example NFL playoffs are on CBS, or a Nevada Wolfpack game (duh the campus is next door and many of your customers GO TO UNR!!!!?????) and staff refuses to change channels from PBS Antique Roadshow or some obscure movie on Syfy channel both showing on MULTIPLE TV'S (Yes they set multiple TVs to TV no one would ever watch then refuse to change it).  So, plan your superbowl workout somewhere else!

     In the black card area they set the TV to Nickelodeon for days so it was showing cartoons to people paying extra to use the area.  REALLY?  The channel in that area changes from time to time but per management (Luke) you cannot request it or any of the TVs to be changed.  This policy is so braindead and just screams corporate ignorance and our rules are more important than our customers.  It's so lazy to not tune in to Nevada Wolfpack and NFL playoffs something your customers would love!!!!

2.  I've never seen any rules enforced.  And if they don't have one for cell phone use WHILE LIFTING they definitely need it.  Saw a guy doing pulldowns with one hand and talking on his phone with the other hand for 5-6 sets and no one does anything.  People everywhere just sitting on machines on their phones.
 
 Also, I've seen multiple people sweating and using the massage equipment then fail to sterilize/wipe off the machines.  

3.  Equipment is often down.  One of the hydro-massage chairs has been down multiple times and one of the employees without me even asking said yeah that chair (1 of 2) seems to be down more than it's not.  Last time i used a treadmill the first 3 were down.

4.  Volume of music is often times way too loud.  Many people ( I would guess half?) wear headphones to try and drown out the sound of the mostly Top 40 (strange mix of music played).  People aren't liking the music you're playing...at least turn it down please?  I have to crank my headphones to not hear their music.

5.  Constant infomercials constantly played on their TVs which are at slightly lower level than the TVs you're trying to watch so it's super distracting.  These TVs constantly remind your your smile is not perfect and you should pay money to fix it.  How does this go with the "no critics" and "no judgement" mottos????  

Finally....management.   Don't leave your business cards for people to contact you if you don't plan to respond to them.  It's embarrassing!  Took multiple emails to get next to no response saying there was nothing they can do about TV's because of corporate.  Asked for a contact at corporate and ZERO response. 

I don't feel valued as a member here.

After my last review, I received an ignorant message from some clown named "Justin C", who probably was a disgruntled employee or maybe just a troll. He said I was fat and mentioned "People's lives and jobs depend on Yelp reviews". Lives? Doubtful. But it got me thinking I never mentioned anything about the service. The service has always been good. The staff is friendly. My issue was with the food quality.

For Christmas I received a $50 giftcard from my employer. So I figured I'd give my old favorite another try. I was in the area tonight and decided to stop in with my boyfriend. Again, the service was flawless. I was disappointed the Shanghai Cucumbers were removed from the menu. But I won't deduct a star for that. They had some new additions to the menu, again. I decided to try the Wok Charred Brussels Sprouts and the Long Life Noodles (Side). The Sprouts were cooked well. They were topped with cilantro which added a nice freshness. The Noodles were tossed with garlic and scallions. They had a great smokey flavor. Overall, I was happy with tonight's dining experience. Plus one star.

Don't believe the prices you pictures you see on here. Everything was different when I went today. 

Mimosas were small...not worth $11. You DON'T get a champagne bottle like they showed. My boyfriend got another drink that was tiny but expensive. 

We waited for a table outside for 25 minutes and another couple ended up moving to it so we had to wait longer....then when we asked for a 4 top instead of a two...we were told absolutely not. Even though we were waiting there for 30 minutes already. Not cool. 

However our waitress was a doll and very sweet. Food was amazing. However the prices for everything is what has me uncomfortable...especially when they won't accommodate your seating. 

So all in all...VERY PRICEY...great food...but everything else could use work.

We have been to this restaurant two times.  On both occasions we had awesome food and equally as fantastic service. I had the Chicken Tikka Marsala and my boyfriend had the Butter Chicken, both were moist and very flavorful.  The staff is very knowledgeable about Indian Cuisine and really take time to explain the menu and any questions you might have (we had a lot!).  The manager, Sharma, could not have been nicer or more accommodating.  He takes the time to talk to each table about their meal and experience.  
We will definitely be back soon! :)
Lauren and Dom

If you love breakfast go to Surrey's! This place is further from the French Quarter it's closer to the garden district. Boy oh boy did we love this place! I had the shrimp and grits which were Delish with a capital D! I had a biscuit instead of the croutons it usually comes with and that was an awesome decision. My boyfriend had the blue crab omelet that you'll see a bunch of pictures of and he loved it! They told us that the bagels are made in house so he ordered an everything bagel and it did not disappoint. To end on a sweet note we spilt the bananas foster French toast.... do yourself the favor and order them!

Jacki's aunts lives down the street and I have been passing by a couple times a year for the past 6 years or so. I finally got my Mom's Deli experience a couple weeks ago when Jacki's aunt, cousin, her bf, and myself were leaving on a road trip to visit her. 

Again (saying this after my Chees-ology review), not what I was expecting inside. I keep setting these expectations for what places will look like on the inside based off of I have no clue. This one was much less suprising. It definitely has the South City, deli, I have been here for a while, we will not renovate, look.

The Mom's Special was delicous. Not out of this world. But the variety of meats and thousand island dressing got the job done. And if I can remember back that far, I believe the tomatoes were surprisingly fresh. It was a little messy and difficult to eat in the car, but if I got to eat and not be the driver, I can't complain too much. The macaroni salad was delicious as well. Jess got a brownie, which was very good, that she so lovingly shared with me. Good start to a great road trip!

Absolutely delicious macarons! Very well made and a quaint atmosphere to enjoy the tasty treats.  My favorite are the vanilla bean and paris tea macarons. This is a must visit patisserie set back in a quiet setting off of main street. $$$$

Just to start out I will say I hate getting my hair cut. I hate waiting and it always just seems like a waste of time for me. I should really shave my head. That being said i usually hit up one of the local sport clips but figured I would try out LJ as I was close by. The self check in is super nice as u don't have to wait for someone to stop what there doing to help u. The waiting area is nice with 4 TV's and nice comfy chairs to sit in.only prob is the TV's are mounted a little low so your view can be blocked, also there is only like 8 chairs so if it gets busy u might be standing. The pricing is kind of confusing as they have a menu in front of u as u sit down "in a nice oversized barber chair" but no prices for anything. I got the normal haircut then was asked if I wanted a shampoo which I agreed then asked for a hot towel which I love. The shampoo was super long I mean it lasted a good 20 mins I feel like. My hot towel was ice cold by time it was done. After that back to chair and got a hot towel on the neck then a straight razor neck shave which was nice all and all it was 24 bucks for everything which is typical but I was there for over an hour and half. Mind u I wasn't in a rush and enjoyed the scupl massage but wow 90 mins seems super long for me when I waited maybe 20 mins to get started.. I will probably go back and just make sure I have a little more time set aside next time.

The best Fresh Mex in town.  Great food and drinks.  Had the Baja Burrito in a bowl.  It was so good, chicken cooked fresh and the black beans seasoning perfectly.  Our fabulous server, Shane was great!!!

I had to come try the mushroom tacos everyone is raving about here on Yelp! I must agree they were delicious. Served on a homemade corn tortilla with a lemony creme fraiche sauce and a semi-spicy salsa were a great compliment to the tacos. Who would think to make mushroom tacos! If you're a mushroom lover like me then you will enjoy these. I highly recommend them. The next item we tried was the flatbread & hummus. They serve both on a very pretty wooden plank. The flatbread itself came out perfectly grilled, and it had some kinda seasoning on top that gave it a hint of flavor. The hummus was perfect! It's very creamy with olive oil drizzled on top. I couldn't stop eating it! 
Last we ordered the margherita pizza. This pizza was perfect with just the right amount of ingredients. It didn't have too much cheese and I was able to dip the ends of the pizza in the hummus to finish that up. The olive oil, tomatoes, and hint of salt were perfect! No complaints here. Can't wait to go back to try more.

This is a friendly accommodating Place run by a husband and wife. It's a little hidden in that it's in the back of an office building off of Oracle. But the food is excellent and the welcome is warm. I think if you like good quantities of well-cooked ethnic food this would be a place you should try.

First time I went here, I was over hyped on the experience and I wasn't excited. 2nd time, very excited! Great food, great bread & butter, awesome wine selection. Only negative was the first time we went, the waiter told me the pasta wasn't made fresh in house. For a top notch restaurant, I want in house fresh pasta, but maybe that's me being overly picky. You go here for the seafood, and the seafood is above reproach! So go for the seafood, be friendly to the wait staff & you just may get a free dessert! I sure did! but I normally get something free everywhere I go!
Delicious, good atmosphere & service. Bread is baked in-house and can be purchased to go!
The people who work here are always so friendly and can help you find whatever you need. I've always gotten my keys cut here and the service is fast and reliable

Top 3 favorite BBQ restaurant in St. Louis! Pulled pork is great, and the fries are so amazing. I suggest the onion rings for an appetizer. Great atmosphere and environment as well. Food takes a while to get to you but it's so well worth the wait!

Over the years, we have relied on purchasing housewares from here.  They always have an up-to-date collection of nearly everything for your living spaces.

The staff is ever-present but also lets you browse with being pushy which I like a lot.  For anyone who has been here before, you can find household items here that you cannot find elsewhere (e.g., tables, lamps, stemware, place settings, etc.) 

This store is located in a south of International Mall.  I would definitely recommend you stop by if you want to upscale your housewares.
Worst Zara. Clothes are a mess and always dirty or ripped. Perpetual 30 minute line you must wait in regardless of what time you go in. Avoid if possible.
While the pool and games were good, the service of bar tenders were not. I don't like being called out on for whatever reason and one of them should be fired for harassing a customer.

I agree with everything you people have said. You can't beat it, the prices are cheap the food is excellent, the rolls are fresh and very very clean. The staff was awesome and service excellent. The location of it is kind of crazy but that's part of the charm i guess. Overall if you couldn't tell I loved it!!

I ordered through yelp and at pickup the food was cold even though I arrived exactly at the time I claimed I was going to pickup the order to go. In addition, when I was ready to pay with cash, the total amount due changed, I was asked to pay more, maybe it was a mandatory tipping charge? Don't make the same mistake I made, speak up and ask for a receipt.
Good food but the prices on the menu are wrong and they cover their azz's by having a barely visible "prices are subject to change" message. Its just not right.

OK, I,m impressed with what's going on at the Co-op!  The aisles are wider and more accessible, the barriers are down, and you can now navigate the place without bumping into someone.  The meat has always been first rate.  I've gotten tenderloin filets a few times and it's great to have them trimmed and be able to pick out a smaller size.  In fact we're having some for my birthday.  Can't wait!  Congratulations, Boise Co-op!  You're getting better and better!  Keep up the good work!
Wait was short, front desk was helpful and patient with waitressing on order. Food was hot and good!

I don't know about you but when my friends and I go out to party until the bar close down we get very hungry.  We usually need food to soak up the booze and at 3:00 in the morning that can be a challenge if you don't know where to go.  The great thing about Denny's is that they are actually opened 24 hours a day!  This is great for all the wasted people in Edmonton.  But you need to tell your Designated Driver to get there before all the other DD's otherwise you will need to wait for a table.  The other great thing about Denny's is you can order breakfast any time of the day, even for dinner if you want!  I love that!  The service is fast and friendly and the prices are pretty sweet considering the amount of food they bring out to you.  You end up feeling like a pig for actually consuming most of the stuff they put in front of you.  But it is all just so yummy that you can't stop packing it in.  If you happen to be drunk we usually tell ourselves that all this food is required to soak up all that booze we consumed.  

Now if you are going to Denny's for breakfast then I suggest one of the following dishes: If you are too hungry for words and love the meat then order the Lumberjack Slam.  If you like omelettes then order the Ultimate Omelette.  The Fabulous French Toast Platter is mighty good if you like your French Toast.  The Pancakes are famous here so defiantly try those.  I like the Heartland Scramble (it comes with the country-fried potatoes... so good).

If you want to order lunch then the Club Sandwich and the Chicken Sandwich is really good. 

If you are actually going there for dinner I can't help you out!  I usually order breakfast for dinner when I got to Denny's just so I can feel like a rebel!

Decent atmosphere and service. The wings are hit  or miss. The definite best thing on the menu is the catfish nugget basket. Great atmosphere for football, just can be sketchy if you are bringing children as some of the patrons don't seem to mind what they say and how loud they say it.

If I were grading the food alone, it would easily be four stars.  The food was lovely - freshly prepared, fresh ingredients and definitely high quality.  

Unfortunately, our experience was marred by very poor customer service.  My best friend ordered the egg and avocado on toast without the toast because she is allergic to gluten.  She asked if some additional vegetables could be added to her meal and was told sternly "No."  

When her food arrived, it had Parmesan cheese on it which was also problematic because she is allergic to cow cheese.  She told the gal who brought it out that she couldn't eat it because of the cheese.  The lady sighed and said "You have to tell them at the front because otherwise they don't know."  (There was no reference on the menu about cheese.)  

We didn't receive napkins with our food so I wandered inside to find some.  I didn't see any and asked the you-can't-add-vegetables lady where to find napkins.  She said "There are napkins on every table."  I pointed to our patio table that had literally nothing on it except our plates.  

"Oh, I guess you don't have any."  

My only other complaint was that we received our coffee and tea well after our food arrived.  

Aside from the attitudinal staff, it seems like a lovely place.  It's clearly very popular and as stated in the beginning of the review, the food was very, very good.  I just think the staff needs some customer service training.

I was a religious costumer for years until recently. I now refuse to even step foot into this place. Whenever I go there the lady at the counter has a constant attitude, she is very rude. Had a bad experience with her when my server didn't do much for us and even messed up both me and my friends order. Went to pay the lady forced me to tip. Telling me I need to tip because she cleaned our table. More recently I went there I asked for the same thing I get every time the lunch special but they make it a dinner special for a few extra dollars. I went to order it when the waitress told me they don't do that. After telling her multiple times I was here a week ago and got it, you guys definitely do it. She argued with me for 5 minutes until she went to a manager and they told her she was wrong. When placing my order I strictly asked for no cucumber because I am allergic in my rolls were cucumbers. About 2 minutes later they come back with my order with all of the cucumbers from my rolls put on the plate. Safe to say they never remade my rolls just threw it off to the side. I will not be returning.

My favorite cafe in all of Indianapolis! Fantastic coffee and great atmosphere. I haven't really tried the pastries but they look yummy. I've tried their breakfast at some point and it was good. More options than your average cafe. Also free Wi-Fi.

The people have spoken, this place is the shiz. 

The coffee is great, the dudes behind the counter are cool and every wonderful thing everyone says about this place is true. I just wanted to add my vote, along with this delicious fact: In the lower level of the coffee shop, every single seat has a designated plug. It's a remote employee's dream!

Good place to go to pick up some products for a little self T.L.C.  This charming little boutique on Walnut offers the finest bath and beauty products and good customer service.  It's not something that I would use everyday, because of the price.  But it's definitely an instant "pick me up" on a gray day.  The natural scents are marvelous, darling.  I love the bath products and there is nothing better than languishing in an hour long bath of their Honey Harvest foaming bubble bath.  And I swear, I instantly feel softer all over after using the shea butter bath creme.  I have not tried their massage products, but they smell so yummy in the store.  Also, I love the organic bar soaps.  Give the place a try!

Had a really delicious meal here tonight with friends. We shared the cheddar dumplings with peach butter - yum. I ordered a couple of small plates, the beef taco and the shredded chicken bbq with cornbread and kale. The taco needed a little something, a sauce, or maybe some cucumber and onion. But the chicken and cornbread was really delicious! And not skimpy size-wise. We shared a couple of desserts, the bread pudding and the peach shortcake. All good. I'll go back!

Terrible service and always out of at least one or two items. Save yourself some time and go elsewhere. I'm completely done with this location. Do everyone a favor and close this disgrace of a location

WOAH! This place is  BEYOND AMAZING! 

I made reservations online, and noted it was my boyfriends birthday. Upon arrival, we were greeted and immediately taken to our table where they had placed 3 birthday balloons for my boyfriend. We had 3 different servers taking care of us the duration of our meal, and they were all fabulous! 

Everything was going great until we got the menus. Now, we've eaten at a fancy place or two, but we had no idea what anything on the menu was (besides the steak). 

We said, "what the hell?" and just ordered the Creole Crawfish Gnocchi (because it stated there was cream cheese somewhere on or in it)  When they brought out our appetizer, it was NOTHING like we had imagined. It looked like it had a mini crab on top (I had never seen a crawfish before). We gave it a try and it was so effin good! So flavorful! We literally left nothing on the plate. 

My boyfriend and I ordered the Filet Mignon of Black Angus Beef. My sister, although skeptical of the dishes on the menu, ordered the Pecan Crusted Gulf Fish. We asked the waitress about the Pecan Crusted Fish and if it was sweet, because the menu said it had crushed corn cream, and we weren't sure if that would be good or not. 

HOLY CRAP! When I took my first bite of my medium rare steak I couldn't believe how tender it was, it was literally melting in my mouth. I asked my sister for a bite of her Pecan Crusted Gulf Fish, and I was literally ok with the idea of dying at that moment. That is the best dish I have ever eaten in my entire life! The crushed cream corn sauce was not sweet at all, it was so buttery and delicious. 

I don't know how these chefs cook dishes that are so beyond amazing, tender, and flavorful, but they did a bitchin job! 

The owner came up to us, introduced himself, wished my boyfriend a happy birthday, and thanked us for coming to his family's restaurant. 

At the end of dinner, we declined dessert, but they brought us a birthday ice cream for the bday boy anyways. 

We could not have had a better experience!!

Lady at the counter was super nice & we had the lunch specials- jerk chicken was just ok (I'm not a fan of bbq sauce used) but the stew meat was delicious; the rice, beans, & coleslaw were nice sides & pretty affordable at $4.99 each.

I have had a mini van since 2002. I have had (2) Kia Sedona's, Ford Free-star, (2) Honda Odyssey's and now a Sienna. I no longer have babies but I am used to the the roominess. I had been looking at a 3rd Odyssey but at the dealership, they wouldn't listen to me or my needs. Sunny V. at Courtesy Toyota LISTENED and HEARD everything I was looking for (not just shaking his head, hearing birdies and seeing dollar signs) and he worked with me until it was perfect! In fact, so perfect that we left with 2 vehicles that night! I have had the van for a month now and have no complaints! It was everything I was looking for and MORE!!!!

To much money for this nasty food. First, it's connected to the Astor Crown hotel and it seems as though it is part of the hotel...wrong! If you try to enter the restaurant from the hotel they tell you to walk towards the front where the hostess stand. It's so uncomfortable walking through all these people to get to the hostess stand only to be turned around and walked through again when your table is available.
So there is your waiter and then there is your drink person. Try to keep up with who is who. So in the beginning I had ordered ceviche but realized I wasn't that hungry and decided to share a plate with my sister. So we're sitting there and then our food comes out. So the ceviche came out even though I cancelled that order. When telling the waitress, she dozed off for a little and then said she didn't hear that I no longer wanted the ceviche anymore. She then says "do you want me to take it back?" To some this may seem weird but to me, when a waiter messes up your order and they bring the wrong food out they apologize and tell you they'll take it off. They thank you for informing them of their mistake. However, she took the food back. The germaphobe in me wanted to know what she was gonna do with that plate. I hope she didn't serve it to the next person that ordered it. Never in my life have I had "mistake" food taken back. 
When I got my correct food, it was drenched in Cajun seasoning. It was almost to overbearing to eat with the 5 jumbo shrimp I was given. The only good thing is when you order a platter they separate it on 2 plates. 
I don't recommend this place to anyone.

We stopped in to purchase a couple of items 2 days ago. My wife asked the cashier to explain how an advertised $5 discount on hand cream would be applied to our purchase. The cashier was very patronizing and unprofessional. We strongly suspect this person is bigoted toward Asian Americans. We will never return to this store again.

The Rolling Chef left me with a few highs and lows. 

I like the price and serving size, $2, and 3 oz. of meat per taco (the fish taco is $3) is a great deal.  The "Jamaican" was delicious. I'd give the Chef 4.5 stars if every taco I tried were as flavorful as this option.  The plantain chips gave it the perfect crunch and the mango sauce in combination with the coconut flakes gave this taco a delicious flavor.  

The remaining two tacos lacked flavor.  The teriyaki sauce on the "Japanese" was waaaaay too strong (Costco prepackaged variety?), and yet the meat lacked any flavor at all.  Rather than aiding the bland meat, the sauce overwhelmed any other flavor with sugary syrup.  The pineapple chunk was huge, but I enjoyed the broccoli slaw on top.  The "Sonoran" was just forgettable.  Bland meat, no spice, yeah, this was an underwhelming selection that could not even be redeemed by the delicious Anita Street tortilla foundation. 

My advice to the novice fusion taco customer is to try the wilder options, like the "Southern" and aforementioned "Jamaican."

Dear Jack Daniels,

I met someone else.  He is newer, younger, and sexier.  He's an Artisan.  You and I had a good run in college, but now I'm a grown-up and I like grown-up things.  

His name is Corsair, and he's lovely.  And he's not just whiskey.  No, he's so much more.  He's gin, and vodka, and absinthe.  He's the best.  His Vanilla Vodka makes me so much happier than you ever could in all the years we spent together.  With Corsair it's different.  Better.  Complex in a good way.

And now that I've had Corsair, I'll never go back.  You just can no longer give me what I need.  And I never understood why you have to live in a dry county.  Corsair lives closer, and his place is awesome.

I hope you understand.

Love,
Me (and probably the rest of Nashville)
I could spend allllll day in this place .. besides that I can and do spend a lot of  here. They have high end items and a great selection of products you can't find in most stores .

I love B.Good. This location is a bit iffy though. There are generally long lines/wait time. I enjoy the almond ginger bowls the most. I also do love knowing where my food is coming from, it's important! 

However, their smoothies are strange. I have tried each one on the menu. The ingredients are delicious don't get me wrong, but the smoothies come room temperature, which is a little off putting. Other than that B.Good has a lot of healthy alternatives, everything is made to order, and they offer customization when it comes to your meal. The staff at this location is nice and always helpful.

This place has very tasty food, fantastic burgers and a terrific pork tenderloin. The appetizer called "Here's to the Heat" is simply delicious, jalapeños halved and filled with cream cheese then wrapped in thick sliced bacon. After flame grilled they are glazed with prickly pear sauce.  I usually eat those with my burger... and it's pretty amazing.
Such a fun time, every time. You can tell that the performers are having such a great time. It's contagious!

We had a great dinner here on Sunday evening around 8 PM. It was very quiet in the restaurant, but the staff was attentive and the food was yummy. I had the teriyaki salmon and it was a lot of food! My boyfriend had sushi rolls and he also likes it. I would recommend this place.

This was my first trip to Eclipse Pizza and I was impressed. I bought a gift certificate on groupon. When we walked in the staff was very friendly. We ordered a Hawaiian calzone & Barbecue Chicken Pizza. The food was fresh and fast. I would definitely go back again.

I attended Revisions 2nd anniversary circus rambler party. They had 2 bands perform, live aerial act and food trucks. All of that was pretty cool. The brewery it self is cool lots of games available to play and the staff is super friendly. Mike F the taproom manager was very attentive and truly made it a great experience. I am not a huge fan of IPAs so I was a little surprised at their on tap menu. They had 13 IPAs, 1 blonde and 3 stouts so if you really like IPAs there are plenty to try there. I tried the darkling stout it was tasty. The overall vibe was great and I am planning on going back when there isnt an event so hopefully can enjoy more.

First of all,the different sides are different. The what I assume is the older side has smaller and nicer pool and hot tub, but the pool wasn't heated during our visit. So, if swimming is something you might consider, the newer side is better.  The hot tub on the older side is smaller, but it looks clean (except for some leaves). The hot tub on the newer side is bigger, has jets, and doesn't look clean (greenish). I a fire pit is something you enjoy, the newer side is better. If you want to go to sleep earlier, don't get a room by the fire pit, because it doesn't close at 10 or 11.  If you just want to look at them, the older side is better. The room sizes are not the same -- despite assurances they are. The biggest problem with the older side is the toilets, which are almost kid sized: too small. They are also inefficient. They claim to be "water wise," but my toilets use less water and never require a second flush. Theirs flush for a longer time and often require a second flush. The doors on the older side don't close themselves, which is convenient sometimes, but a security threat others. 

The beds in the older side were also harder and not comfortable. There was a smell in the older side, which caused me to have to open the door despite the cold temperature outside, but eventually I had to close it because it was getting too cold.
Great Burgers and frozen custard!  My favorite concrete is Blackberries and marshmallow fluff, it's insane!

Bought a living social coupon $10 for $20 in food
Bill came. .. server said we do not honor this promotion.  He gave me $6 off... he was lucky I had the $19 cash.... no tip because did not have any cash left! 
Food was amazing

Have tried fast food twice at west Edmonton mall and will keep going back cos food is fresh, tastes good and price is very reasonable, had the pho with beef all, spring roll vermicelli bowl and u must try the Vietnamese iced coffee Yummy..... try it!!!!!
DS
Average, blend food and bad service. I stop here only if I'm in a hurry and need something quick to take out other than that I stay away!
Had a good experience. Cashier was friendly and courteous. Got chicken empanadas and fries. Tasted great and wait was short on what was a busy day.

Great lunch options and happy hour. Their cerviche is stellar.  The fish and shrimp sandwiches and wraps are delicious. Solid beer selection and lots of drink specials.
The sunday all you can eat brunch seems to be a fantastic deal, and the offerings look great, but i've never partook.  

The dinner options seemed ehhh.  The plates are small-ish and the prices are a touch high.  for small plates.

If you're looking for crepes, whether savory or sweet, the Perch is a great local place to go. I ordered one with blue cheese, prosciutto, walnuts, and a balsamic glaze and it was what I needed in the morning. Coffee is fresh and the service is fast!
Great food.  The service was relatively slow but the food more than made up for it.  I wasn't so sure about the area but the little courtyard the place has is a great place for a meal.

Love this place! Came here for my birthday with good friends. They have an app you can download and add your name to the waiting list which I'm super glad I did because they were packed! As soon as I got there our table was ready! Very convenient! The tacos are so good! I had the pork belly and baha fish. The pork belly is tender and flavorful. Baha fish was crispy and good. The grilled corn is amazing. The only complaint I had was the service was kinda slow and they kept bringing our food out one at a time. I had ordered pork tamales and it was only one small tamale that they brought on a plate by itself before our food came. It was so small and totally not worth the price. Very disappointing. Overall this place is trendy and the atmosphere is nice. Love the outdoor dining! Kid friendly. Parking is kind of hard but if you get lucky you can park on the side streets.
Outstanding customer service.   We were both impressed with the personal attention and genuine interest in resolving our concerns with the car. Will bring our cars here from now on.

This is mostly a review about their new Beyond Tacos. I was so happy to hear they've got a meat free 100% plant based option now so I had to go check them out. The taco is more expensive than the regular beef ones but I'm guessing the price might come down if/when the fine folks at Beyond Meat expand. 

That said the taco was DELICIOUS! It's got the prefect amount of sauce/spices. Apparently they're cooked separately from the meat so no worries there. If you're a meat eater I'd suggest you give it a try as I'm not sure you'd be able to tell the difference and if you're a veggie, it's always nice to have more options so give it a try!

According to their website you can sub out the Beyond Meat for any of their meat options so I might do that next time.

A bit about the location, it's clean and there's plenty of room. The employees are kind of a bit meh about being there but they're polite and quick. The new Greyhound station is right next door so you're likely to find a few random people hanging around. No biggie but just a heads up.

I ordered Golden Triangle apps and the pad Thai (requesting gluten-free). The restaurant was so attentive and made sure that my  requests were honored, but did not sacrifice my needs for incredible flavor. 

This was some of the best Thai food I've ever tasted and by far the best in Philadelphia (And I've tried quite a lot since being bored over quarantine with little motivation to cook!)

Not to mention, the owner, whose name is escaping me, was so friendly, warm and professional. I cannot wait to come back here for both pickup and once in-person dining is allowed indoors.

So I found this place because a friend came into town and wanted to try some place up north. This place looks kinda dive from the outside but the food is great. They make all of the food when you order it and they have lunch specials that will fill you up. It was fairly cheap too.

The location is awesome, right by the Delaware river. The atmosphere, the energy of the restaurant and bar was good. But... the food is mediocre, especially considering the pizzazz it tries to exude. 

It's really not my kind of place, and will only go again if someone was taking me there. It is kinda in the middle of nowhere, so be sure to have a DD.

Mississippi Nights seems as shady as that site Claire mentions, but historically has drawn the bands and crowds follow.

Inside, the place is dingy, segregated for shows including underage crowds, and not tiered enough to afford most patrons a clear view. I prefer other local venues, but you don't get to pick where the band plays.

The Chaik is open for business! And it's the perfect getaway in the far NE corner of Philly, aka the 'hood for Eastern European eats. No doubt, they easily stick out on the main street, and the lush grape vines lining the entrance way only make it more curiously inviting. They have ample outdoor seating (front and back) for all your Covid social distancing needs. Sink by the entrance to wash hands, too. Understandably, the prices have recently increased by 15-20%. The waiter kindly let us know beforehand, since it wasn't on their menu. Foods were served on disposable plastic and wood plates.

On to the food. It's hard not to love a buttered toasty warm bread for starters, but there's more delicious carbs and meats coming. The Lula kebab is like a beef-lamb burger patty, rebelliously served on a spear. Every country has its own style, but I am definitely digging the spears. Uzbek pilaf makes a good balance to other richer dishes. The lagman soup/noodles are good, too, thick and chewy.

I have been trying to sell my car so every Saturday I bring her here for a car wash.  For the same price as Crew, you get the interior cleaned as well.  This keeps you from having to pay more to vacuum and then extra time to wipe it down.  It isn't a full detail, so you may have to do a bit extra if you are wanting that, but you can't beat the price for what you get!

I had my first gyno appointment at this office. After going through their website meticulously to make sure that it would be free under my insurance, as my annual gyno appointment, I came in for my appointment. The desk staff was professional and efficient, as was the nurse. I enjoyed my entire experience - something I never thought I would walk away from an obgyn appointment saying! My doctor, in particular, I found phenomenal. Dr. McGinty was personable and made me feel very comfortable. She was professional and clearly qualified. When I had some blood drawn for a test, the nurse who came in and took my blood was incredible. Albeit, it may sound odd to rave about a blood draw, but having had my blood taken previously this month by a medical professional whose only job was to take blood, the nurse who performed the blood draw at the Women's Wellness Center was much quicker, pain free, and all-around better! I couldn't believe how fast she worked. 

While I have seen reviews saying they had to wait on the phone when calling for an appointment, this was not my experience at all. I called and was immediately answered, and then penciled in for an evening appointment later the same week! In short, I found my experience pleasant and professional. The office is in a row home as well, which provided an aesthetic experience I much preferred to it's more typical overly-sterile feeling counterpart.

Not spectacular, but very good.  A small, focused, approachable menu priced fairly cheap made by the top chef team in Philly.  There's a definite beer focus here too.  Certainly nothing wrong with that.

My girlfriend and I decided to skip the pizza and try some of the limited other options.  She had two rotolos which were really nice.  Flakey, gooey, nutty, cheesy.  Two was enough for her, but she is admittedly quite tiny so if you're a big larger like me and want to make a meal of these 3 would probably be a safer bet.

I had the calzone which was freakin' massive but I finished the whole thing thankyouverymuch.  Not that I should be proud of that but I was.  Gloating my gluttony until I noticed the two boys next to me housing a stupid Nutella pizza for dessert.  Fabulous.

I always come to this bar and lounge to get an salmon platter. In addition, I once in a while get an Mango Long Island Ice Tea. I have to say Daveon made all the attempts beyond a bartender to check on the customer and serve me well. Her professionalism and her positive attitude supports your business highly and how she enjoys her job. Good job.

Professional, warm and welcoming salon. Mena bent over backward to accommodate me in late fall of 2016 for a major event just 24 hours before, even though I'd never been in her salon. She rearranged the schedule to fit me in for full highlights with Mandy, who did a phenomenal job. Every employee was gracious and sweet. The salon is modern and clean. They did an excellent job both on the service and on explanation of different products without being pushy about purchasing the products. A big city salon at small town prices and definitely worth booking if you're looking for a new stylist.

My husband and I just moved to Tampa, and this is the first place we went because the reviews were high. Tanika instantly put a smile on our face and brightened our morning, and the food was delicious! Very unique take on Avocado toast, and pastries galore.

There are not many good sushi restaurants available. We previously used another local restaurant until they changed prices and portions without reflecting it on their menu. Anyhow, this sushi was affordable (still running their grand opening special pricing) and DELICIOUS. So fresh and so appetizing, we got takeout and were pleasantly surprised by the entire experience from ordering online to bringing it home, easy as pie. I cannot say enough but I will be going back one million more times ! Thank you Sushi X for opening here!

The food here is fantastic! I had the falafel sandwich and hummus and it was truly delicious. Their restaurant is easy to miss on 73 and a quick turn, but the outside and inside are nicely decorated and super clean. They also have hookah during the summertime, which is a major bonus. The host was super friendly and knowledgeable regarding what foods would suit my vegan needs. I can't wait to come back with my boyfriend and friends!
This is our favorite pizza place in the area. The white Giardino white pizza and gyros are our go-to offerings.

Dined here again last week. Took some visitors from Germany. The food was exemplary! Even the 15 year old with loved her meal! I had catfish with broccoli accompaniments. Wow! Words cannot do justice. We dined on the patio. Beautiful! An awning provided shade until dusk. What a lovely experience.
I would love to give a 5, but I have to take away a bit for ambience. About 15 minutes before we left (thankfully it took that long) a party with three (totally age-inappropriate) young children was seated right next to us. I seriously mourn the days when it was the standard in American society to acknowledge the concept of age-appropriateness...on the part of parents and restaurant management. Also, as we were leaving, I noticed the upstairs dining rooms were very loud. Each had tables with small children, and some with just simply loud adults. The last time we dined here, we were in an upstairs dining room and the noise level was quite loud, as opposed to the times we have dined downstairs at the tables with a view of the garden. For me the experience was devalued by the noise.
I love this restaurant, and without reservation recommend the food, but if you care about a pleasant, sophisticated, quiet experience, you need to take certain measures to perhaps enhance your chances of acheiving the desired atmosphere. I would suggest perhaps requesting downstairs dining and adding that you value a pleasant ambience.
I am all for a movement demanding restauranteurs start again respecting the sensibilities of those who want excellent food AND ambience for their dining-out dollar.  
Somebody has to start fighting the downgrade in sophistication in our society.
Simply the best. Every. Single. Time. Took some friends here for a birthday celebration and was not disappointed. Impeccable service and gorgeous food.
Great selection and flavor. Friendly staff. They let you sample before you buy. I love the fire on the mountain and the Bloody Mary jerky.
Ordered $50 worth of food for 10 people and they had it all made fresh and correct in 7 mins!!! Best fast food experience ever!

While the pasta with "olive oil" and veggies (yep, bland as it sounds) and shoestring frittes still earned a hearty "meh!" I'm adding a star because the staff is excellent. Tara channeled Fran Dreisher for us, and had us rolling out of our banquette.

What a flashback to my childhood.. Fantastic dessert spot, and very inexpensive.

GO get you some ice cream!
My husband I I moved here a few years ago from NY and have been looking for a great seafood market. We found one! This place is the best! We don't buy our seafood anywhere but here.
Never fails to disappoint.  Either it takes 78 minutes for two 10" pizzas, or the pizza has the wrong sauce.  Or, the evening is shot, just waiting for pasta or chicken... Time to give up.

I had been at the U of A for quite a while now, and seeing this current location get replaced three times(bad business location?) and finally comes down to Fuku Sushi.

My wife and I went in to give it a try this afternoon around 1 pm and was just in time for their lunch speical ( up to 2 pm). We were not seated, and after a while they told us to sit whereever, we went to sit on the side sofa which was not cleaned. They saw me wiping the table and figured I got it taken care of so they didn't offer to clean our table once. We ordered Vegas roll, spicy tuna roll, spicy scallop / spicy tuna hand rolls and 7 piece of tuna sashimi. It totalled up to around $35 + tips.

The only thing we remembered about the rolls were its tiny size, the spicy tuna was not spicy and neither was the scallop. The scallop was kinda raw and it tasted like it was just defrosted.  The sashimi were cut wrongly and it did not taste fresh at all.

Though there were not many people in the restuaruant, they still had us wait for 20 minutes, the music was ok, but way too loud. Few flat screen TV on both sides of the walls broadcasting sports and the servers were friendly. 

0/1 service / environment
0.5/4 food taste experience

I would not come back to this place unless you are more for the drinks. They have happy hours at 3pm~6pm.

Great authentic Italian food. Serving sizes, very good portions. BYOB wine. Great service  there were 10 of us for dinner on Saturday night. The bread comes out first and it just keeps getting better and better after that. Garlic rolls and bruschetta, salad then entrées. You want to go with lots of people in order to share. My Saltambucca was marvelous.
This place is better than most cafes and bakeries in Europe, NYC or LA! Don't miss the cafe or the next door bakery or both!!!

My son ordered fried pickles. They were soggy and overly oily; mostly soggy. 
Daughter cheeseburger was good. 
My son ordered popcorn shrimp and they were as good as could be expected. 
I ordered wing traditional and asked for them crispy. 5 of them were perfect. The other 10 were chewy. I always ask for crispy because they always seem a little under cooked and the skin chewy.

I need to report an assault!  Seriously though, the Hot Chicken Po'Boy isn't messing around.  If you do not specify (order up did not give us the option) you get the "Nashville Hot" level of spicy.  It's uncomfortably spicy.  My coworkers and I ordered it today and there was coughing, sweating, and crying all around.  Ok so it wasn't INEDIBLE but I will definitely never order it at work again. Piggy chips are awesome and their chicken is always perfectly crispy fried.  I'm a general fan but wish someone had warned me about the spice! Side note, I like spicy things and order spicy food often. This sandwich really surprised me. If you order it, wear chapstick. The bar is a great place to watch a game.
We miss you up here in Farmington Hills!! Always enjoyed your food and how nice you all are. Blessings on you all.

I ate here last night for the first time and it was amazing! I've had Indian food before, but Tiffin Elkins Park is by far the best place I've been to yet. The butter chicken was delicious and the portions were generous. The staff was extremely helpful and kind. I will be coming back for sure!

Quiet, spacious dessert spot that serves ice cream martinis, specialty sundaes and cocktails. The sundaes here are delicious! You can mix em up as you wish or you can go for the specials on the menu. I tried the Nutty Espresso. For 5.99$, the sundae is a steal. 

If you are not in the mood to indulge, they serve baby sized sundaes for 2$. Either way they are all about generous portions, great taste and happy customers. Highly recommended

Showed up expecting that reservations had been made for a group event a half hour before closing on a Sunday. Snafu with reservations, manager did everything possible to seat us and feed us. Great service and great manager. Portions were good size and food was tasty. Cost was Not $$ but $$$.

My only issue is not really with the store, but with the category that this is a store that carries men's clothes.  It's really just an afterthought, and covers only about 10% of the store.

Their selection of ladies wear looks to be pretty decent, and store isn't any worse than most second hand or liquidators.  But I feel like my time was wasted with the claim that this place carries men's clothing, when the selection is so thin, it's not really worth it.

As a vegan & thai food lover, I love Thai L'Elephant. My husband eats meat, but yet usually will eat off of the vegan menu because it's that good. The fuji apple dumplings are a delicious way to start! I mix up my entree order between the Le Grande, Basil Mock Duck, and Holy Basil. All are delicious! When living in Phoenixville we ordered it to go, however I much prefer going in and eating it than having it for take out. We've sinced moved a bit away from the area, but will always make the trek back for their delicious thai food!

The wait time can be a bit frustrating but we had no problem since we got there in the afternoon. We ordered fresh and chargrilled oyster and fried crawfish tail. The oyster was so fresh it could jump back to the ocean. Chargrilled is too salty and dry for me. The crawfish tail is decent. The cocktail sauce was so good compared to nearby places.

My boyfriend and I stumbled on Martin's as we were walking around downtown Nashville, and I'm glad we got the experience. We got into line a little before 8 on a Sunday night, and we spent about a half hour in line, but that was the longest part of the process. The service was so quick and efficient that we waited maybe 10 minutes for our food.

The atmosphere was lively; we sat downstairs, but we could still hear the live band playing on the rooftop deck, which was a nice touch for those who wanted to keep away from the smoke pits upstairs. 

Now for the food. We ordered the Big Brother sampler to split, as neither of us were hungry enough for an entire order of anything, and the BF isn't much into barbeque anything. The Big Brother sampler comes with smoked brisket, ribs, and two sides (we had hushpuppies and mac & cheese). The sides were fantastic: there were seasoned breadcrumbs on the mac which added a great touch, and the hushpuppies were bomb. However, the brisket and ribs were just okay. The rub on the ribs was good, and the meat definitely fell off the bones, but it wasn't anything to write home about. The brisket was well smoked but beyond that didn't have much flavor. Each table comes with a huge bottle of Jack's BBQ sauce, which definitely boosted the flavor of the brisket.

Overall, I was hovering between a 3.5 or 4 out of 5, so I did the correct math thing and rounded up. If you're in town, give it a try.

I was visiting GSR for 3nights/4days with my wife and 2 kids on the thanksgiving weekend.
The hotel looks great; the complimentary valet parking and bell services are very efficient.
The check-in line was too long and slow for my opinion. Only 2 front desk stations were attended and waiting in the line after 4 hours driving with the kids was not pleasant.
The kid's play areas were great. A very nice play place next to an arcade area. We also tried the onsite bowling and it was great. My kids loved it. (Every activity cost). 
The room was another story. I often use hotels/inns for my business travels and expected little bit more from GSR. Basic things were missing here.
The room was very dark. Only two very low light table lamps were in the room. I used to lowlights in hotel rooms however this was too much.
The lack of light continue in the bathroom, there was a low light next to mirror and one head lamp that operated by timer that turn light off after the setting time (be careful not to set it too short before ending your shower :-) ) and it took 2-3 minutes to the bulb to warm up and give a reasonable light!!! So old fashion.
Cleanliness - There were used tissues, old pens and notes papers between beds and nightstand that was not cleaned during all our stay.  If talking about the nightstand there was only one night stand. I took 2 queen size beds in the room and the night stand was in the middle between the beds, so only one side of bed can use it. me and my wife wearing glasses so it was very inconvenient.
There were no cups in bathroom to wash mouth or stand the toothbrush.
No places to hang towels, only one small hook behind door that was hanging and about to fall from the door any moment. (the funny thing it says as other hotels I can keep towels for reuse if I won't put them on floor, I usually do that, however how should I dry them if there is no place to hang them?)
No Bar or refrigerator in room which is kind of standard in other places.
I would definitely think twice before coming back. I may give it another chance next time I get to Reno as my kids enjoyed it so much but I doubt it.

The place is great there is so much prizes to win in the claw machine and games to play. The only bad thing is this one employee, Matt. I was playing the claw machine and the prize got stuck in the claw. So I went over to the assistance table to get some help, so Matt was there and he came to help me. He then preceded to try and get the prize without opening the glass window, which confused me but it didn't work so he eventually opened it up and that was it. The claw machine had another prize stuck and then I asked Matt to help me again. Matt comes over and looks at me, then he calls his manager over saying that the prize shouldn't be mine. It was the machine fault Matt, there was no way to get it. So then the manager just gave me the prize and then Matt walked away. I cleared the machine so I asked Matt again to refill the machine. He was groaning and obviously didn't care about it at all. I also asked him if he could put in a certain prize so I can try to get it. He ignored me, and I even pointed out to him what prize and he just didn't say anything. So I just played and I cleared the machine again. Calling Matt over again since he was the only one there, he put the prize in unfair ways which made most of them in a dead zone where the claw can't reach them. I tired for the ones that were achievable, but he put the prize in such a way in fell down behind the prize grab area. So I was pissed so I left. The thing to take away from this is, don't let Matt help you with anything. If you see him, try and get someone else to help you. He is by far the worst person in Round 1, everyone else is so nice. This one guy Matt, avoid him cause he is just gonna make you have a bad time.

Last time I went, there was a hair in my salad. :( i saw it the minute my salad was set down and i went to fork some lettuce. i didn't say anything because its always SO embarrassing and it is just a hair. BUT... it is someone elses hair....arent the people preparing food wearing hairnets? Thats whats concerning to me. And to bring this out to a customer and not notice..do you not check dishes before presenting them? Definitely changed my view on this place.

I think it is an improvement from Katz (which always annoyed me because they didn't spell the name right) - and I will re-edit this review after a 2nd go around. But what took me back today was when I was in the drive thru and ordered a 1 Medium coffee with cream and 2 sugars. 

I was impressed when I drove up and noticed they use Hub Coffee (which is great coffee) - they lady in the drive thru handed me my coffee and two sugars. Typically, they should add them for you (hence I was in a drive thru) and she didn't even give me stir sticks. Seemed, odd. I asked her if she could add them and she looked puzzled. No body was behind me, no body was at the register, but she gave me a funny look. I wonder how many other people this has happened too. 

Again, I will re-vamp this review when I drive out to say hi to my folks and see if they do better a 2nd time. I do support local business. . . but this was just lack of training on the managers part.

for $25, you get both mani and pedi!  and it's not half bad. actually, i've tried almost everything in philadelphia on the cheaper end (hey, i'm a student now!!) and this is by far the best. i can vouch for that. just make sure you bring your own nail color (read: polish selection is not enviable) and make sure you call before you get there so you won't be stuck in a long line. enjoy!

This place is no frills, but provides reliable, fast service. The staff has been here since forever (ok, slight exaggeration) and they are always consistent.
I usually get the green curry, broken rice & pork chop or pho when I come here. Today I decided to be adventurous and try their bun bo hue, since I'm currently obsessed with that broth.
The broth was cleaner than Pho Saigon's, but I did not enjoy the pig's feet. It was not as tender, which I was bummed. However, the broth was delicious...so I can make an exception. I also tried my friend's shrimp green curry and the beef & peppers dishes which were so, so, so tasty...wish I got that instead!

During the height of the Covid-19 pandemic my skin suffered, I washed and moisturized, but that's it. I was in need of a deep cleaning facial so I went to City Hydration to try their new Platinum Hydrafacial and let me tell you it did not disappoint! First of all the space is gorgeous and smells great, I was kindly greeted by the staff as soon as I walked in which made me feel welcomed and comfortable. I was then taken to a private room where a masked & gloved technician completed my facial. The facial consists of several steps and took about an hour.  She explained everything as she went, but still allowed me to relax which made all the difference for me! Pores clean, face lifted and skin tightened! I could feel it working! And when the treatment was complete my skin was literally glowing.  I wasn't going to write a long review but businesses deserve a special shout out when they're doing it right...especially during covid-19. I would definitely recommend city hydration and the Hydrafacial, especially if you haven't had a facial in a while.

Working with Dr. Walling. Excellent care from him. X-rays do take time because the place is busy!  But not an exceptionally long time and well within the window that I allow from check in. 
CT scans and MRIs have been extremely efficient ( usually taking less time than scheduled) !  Staff is very friendly. 

It is a hospital setting so will never be a place I want to go 'hang out' but the care is excellent.

I want to sing the praises of Ivan, one of the property managers there. When I met him for the initial walk-through, his energy was awesome, very welcoming and friendly, and he went out of his way to show me the place, never in a rush. 

Then, while I was applying for a place online, someone else came in person and put money down on the same apartment, so that when I finished my online application it said that the apartment was no longer available. Ivan called me and told me he would see what he could do to possibly accommodate both myself and the other new tenant. He called me multiple times, checking in with me about where he was in the process, and by the next day, he had arranged it so that both applications were honored. 

Ivan is the best kind of property manager one could hope for, and he's a big part of what made me want to moving to Patterson Place apartments...it's always important to know that there are good people in the management office of where you are renting, and Ivan is as good as they come. Kind, friendly, understanding, asks good questions and seeks to understand, and works hard. Thank you, Ivan!

All of their margaritas are so tasty but my favorite definitely has to be their mango! I highly recommend any of them.
I've got their oysters every time I've went and never been disappointed. They're always fresh and only $1 during their happy hour everyday from 3:00pm-6:00pm.
I highly recommend getting their corn as a side. Wont regret it. Has got so much flavor!

Slowest place I've ever been to in the morning on the way to work. Food tasted like Poison, so the kitchen things must not get cleaned and my ice tea was watered down. The only employee working there was also miserable. Worst Dunkin ever.

Food was delicious.  I got the chicken and waffles.  Only reason they got 4 stars instead of 5 is that we didn't go at a busy time and you could tell the food had been sitting a while.  Also, the water machine mixes some fruit punch with your water (unavoidable and when I asked they said the back machine also does it so you can't get a clean cup of water).

Also breading on our chicken was non existent and fries were cold.  Even with that the food was still very good.  Just need to step up the kitchen staff and food production.

Stopped in for a mini canolli but kiddo wanted a $4.25 slab (huge slice) of REAL Italian cheese cake.  Divine.

We love Donna and the staff here.

We just can't say enough great things about the REAL Italian desserts baked here.
And thanksgiving pies for $8 - $15 that beat the crap out of Linvilla (Sorry Linvilla - we love you too - but for pies you gotta try Viso's.).

And don't miss $1 canolli day (get in line early and bring cash) every summer.

Don't ever go here! They can never make orders correctly and then catch an attitude when you tell them about it. That's why they have the "Now hiring" no experience needed sign. On top of that I just came from here, they couldn't even break a $20 bill through the drive thru and then gonna get upset at me smh

I thought long and hard about posting this review. I honestly do feel as though the way I was treated had to do with the fact that I am 24 years old. But I paid Eric Krebs good money for the work done on my car, and realized that the level of service I received was unacceptable.

I took my car in to get fixed (had no idea what was wrong with it). It was a busy day, so I was told that my car would probably not be looked at until the end of the day and they would call me. Totally fine. Turns out my car needed a new battery. Easy fix and my car would be ready in  no time. They would call me when it was ready. 

Except I never got called. I waited a day and a half before calling and was finally told that they were having trouble finding my car battery and would be in touch when they found it.

Of course they never called me back. When I called, this time it was that the tube connecting the battery to my car was the wrong size. I did get ONE call though! This time they finally had all the correct parts and promised to be in touch once my car was ready to go. I called them two days later and they said my car was ready, but I had to hurry because they closed in less than an hour!

When I went inside to pay, I was presented with a bill that was around $50 more than I was quoted. I was told that this was for their "time and effort" looking for the tube! I didn't think that that was a mistake that I had to pay for, but rather than argue, I quickly paid my bill and left. I had already been without a car for several weeks at this point, the last week being spent at Eric Krebs. 

There are many, many, many auto repair shops in the Santa Barbara/Goleta area. Support one that treats their customers fairly, regardless of their age.

Seriously. This place is amazing

Chicken sandwich is #1 
BBQ burger 2nd fav 
Regular burger 
Bologna sandwich 

June update: we've now been over 10 times. I seriously can't get enough of this place.

I still consider driving multiple hours to have one of these burritos (even when I am not intoxicated), and it still tastes just as good (as it does when I am intoxicated).

Yeah the prices go up every week, but now that I am no longer a student I can find a way to afford it.

I was in Philly for a business meeting that finished earlier than expected, and before I drove home I thought I'd check out the sights.  So I stopped in at the visitor's center, and the lady at the desk suggested their trolley tour.  Having done a similar tour in San Francisco and having really enjoyed it, I signed up.   As it's the off season, there was only one other person on the trolley with me, so we had the undivided attention of the tour guide, which would have been nice if he had actually had any real knowledge of the sights.  Instead he resorted to lame jokes and pointed out things like the 7-11, saying "That was NOT here when the Constitution was written."  I know it was an attempt to be funny, but it just fell flat.   

Since this is one of those tours where you can get off, do your thing, then get back on when it comes back around, we picked up a couple of other people along the way.  One woman was from Australia and had several questions, none of which he had an answer for.  At one point she even asked him "Are you not going to give us any information about these places like the guy on the other bus did?"  He then said "What do you want to know?"  Seriously?  He's paid to do this every single day, and he doesn't know what to tell the tourists?  Don't they have a script they're supposed to work from, or a test they have to pass to do this?  

On the plus side, the guide did make an excellent recommendation for a Philly cheesesteak, although he did tell me that he only gets them about once a year.  Maybe this tour is better during their regular season, when the guides are all warmed up from working with several tourists, but this was not a great experience at all.
Food was okay, service is rough but can't fault the waitress as it appeared she was only one working.  Likely won't come back.

"Broth is comparable to pho spots in San Jose California"- my buddy during our trip to Reno who lives in SJ 

SO like I mentioned in my other review of another place sort of nearby... the broth is what makes pho PHO 

The broth!! 
This place has an amazing body of the soup, flavors just there and when you add the "green onion oil" nuac beo" you bowl becomes complete!! Like I said before not for the faint who are watching their figures. 

Let's rewind... And go over 5 things 

Atmosphere 5/5 feels like a SJ hole in a wall
Distance to downtown 5/5 just the outskirts 
Cleanliness 3/5 
Food quality 5/5 
Staff friendliness 5/5

So I've ate here a handful of times and the pho broth has been very consistent! The noodles seem to be cooked perfect not over cooked and the typical pho dat biet is excellent. Last time I was here I tried their ox tail bowl and it was so tender!!!! Almost fall off the bone! 

What blows me away is the pricing! Super cheap compared to bay pricing usually ranging from 11-15 a bowl. This place is still sub 10 bucks!!! Insane!!! And the quality is there. That alone bumps up my rating. 

Location? It's in a off beat old strip mall. Definitely can drive by it and not know it's there!! But what I've learned is the hole in the wall areas are the best spots!!! And this stands true to my statement. 

I've tried their appetizers from fried chicken wings to spring roll and egg rolls all tasty and they come out in a fair amount of time. What makes a restaurant perfect is the timing of the bowls delivery to the table. They served our group of 10 at the same time and all the bowls look and seemed consistent in food temp and noodle texture. Everyone was talking and as soon as the food was served it became utter silence!  If you eat pho enough you know when your noodles are over cooked. Soggy and it can definitely ruin your noodle experience.

Well all that's being said it's safe to say that I'm a fan of this place and will come back when I'm in town and have the craving for pho! 

I'd recommend this spot if you are looking for a great bowl!!!

We had Rittenhouse Handyman install 2 ceiling fans for us in July of last year. We purchased a variety of braces and fan-rated junction boxes to have available for the install because we were replacing simple light fixtures and weren't sure what was up there. The installation seemed to go well and the installers told us the existing junction box was already fan-rated and, lucky us, we didn't need to do that extra work! We happily returned the supplies we had purchased. Unfortunately, we immediately had problems with one of the fans - a burning-type smell as well as a shaking/shuddering. I reached out to Rittenhouse Handyman and, to their credit, they promptly sent the guys back to look at it. They essentially told me the issues were due to the uneven ceilings in our 100-year-old rowhome and the fact that we bought lower-priced fans. Both of these things happened to be true, so I said thank you and they went on their way. However, we soon found out the burning smell was due to the fan being installed to a light switch with a dimmer, which if you aren't aware (which we weren't) is a bigtime no-no and fire hazard. Again, to be fair, I recognize these guys aren't electricians but I feel like they should have known this and pointed it out so we could remedy it with the proper contractor! Fortunately I caught the issue myself with a quick google search and we called an actual electrician and had the problem fixed right away. 
   As for the shuddering, we continued to chalk this up to their comment we had bought low-priced fans, so we finally bit the bullet and purchased 2 new, high end fans this week. We had the electrician come back out to install and to my dismay, he pointed out (and showed me) that the junction boxes were in fact NOT fan-rated and the ceiling fans could have fallen down at any time. This is especially alarming because one fan sat directly above my 3-month-old's play mat in her nursery. 
   I encourage Rittenhouse Handyman to be more attentive. Both the dimmer switches and junction box issues should have been on their radar and if they had felt that addressing these issues was outside their scope of service they never should have accepted the job.

This is generally my first place to find shoes.  they have a huge selection.  you will find quality shoes for a good price.  Generally i go right to the back of the store, and start in the clearance section.  it is totally worth it. if i had the money i would buy shoes here everyday.
Its name brand shoes, so you wont find walmart prices or anything, but you will get a good deal for what you buy.  
Its overwhelming at times because of the huge selection and open floor area, it can feel like you will never get through them all, but i love the fact i just look below the shoes and find my own size. 
I am a DSW reward member, and i do use their coupons when i remember in time.  The last time i was in there i used an expires rewards member coupon, and i was excited to save the 10 dollars.  
I love a place that will accept expired coupons(within reason).

I love the atmosphere. The dim lights and warm colors, cumfy chairs creates a lovely place to meet your community, sit quietly or enjoy coffee with your pals. 

My favorite part I must say is the 1.25 beers on Wednesday's every week. They have a delicious selection of beer. The drinks are comparably priced to those stupid chain places. The only thing that is missing from this conveniently located establishment is music. Where is it? I would love to hear something other than crickets. Doesn't have to be live even though I hear they do offer live music once in awhile. Some form of music would make this place even more perfect.

Stopped by during lunch time and it was obviously packed. I wanted to try something new so I ordered the cheeseburger sliders and waffle fries. The burgers were juicy with every bite and the waffle fries were surprisingly good with some added seasoning. I look forward to coming back and trying their pork sandwich sliders.

I used to like this restaurant especially their fried chicken and their grilled Meats. I came tonight at 7:30 and all the food had been sitting without being stirred or replenished. They said they close at 9 p.m. so I should have been told that the food would not be changed when I paid to enter. I took the manager out of his office and walked him around and showed him all the food. I told him it's real simple you just stir it and make sure that the food stays moist so that it looks appealing. The meats were dry because they have sat too long. So they weren't edible at all. It's too bad the brisket looked good until it was cut. Unfortunately I had already paid and they didn't offer a refund despite the fact that the manager agreed the food all looked bad. I'm done. Decent places would have decent food in this place definitely does not have that

European wax center's facility makes you feel like your in a professional salon. I went here for my first Brazilian today and the people were super friendly and informative it hurt because it was my first time but my waxer was very knowledgable on which places hurt the most and told me the worst was over. She made me feel very comfortable. They also use a different type of wax that is hard to hurts way less. I can't wait to go back and get other place done now !
Stopped in and hit HH, ordered a Tavern Burger, had an IPA, ok maybe 3.....enjoyed all of it. Fun place to spend time after a long day. Staff is attentive. Looking forward to my next visit.

The pastries here are amazing. 
Breakfast sandwiches are hearty and filling. 

Came for lunch and of course the line was at the door, I suggest ordering ahead. 
I typically order pastellios (carne queso, carne) heard the shrimp ones are good. They also typically have rice (white and Spanish rice), shredded pork, plantains, tostones, beans etc pretty much everything. I've also had the mofongo from here in the past and it was really good.
The elderly lady in there yells at costumers for no reason. Not worth it

Family Fence did a great job! They came over quickly to give me a estimate and were able to get me scheduled on a day that worked for me. They arrived first thing in the morning and built 600ft of fence in less than 8hrs. They had several men here that worked hard all day long. I am very happy with my fence!! I highly recommend Family Fence!

If you like delicious, well-prepared food, definitely check this place out.  Make sure that at least one person gets the roast chicken, so that everyone can try some - it was the best thing we had, by far.  The cheese plate was very good, although I would recommend that they serve it on a smaller plate so the chunks don't look so small relative to the size of the plate.  Our server (Tristan) was great, steering us toward a better wine choice and entrees that we cleaned off our plates.  The only thing that kept Miel from being five stars in my ranking is that the ambiance is more of a foodie restaurant than a full-on fine-dining experience.

I used to be a regular customer (once or twice a week). Last week I spent so money on wing zings and when they were delivered they were less than two inches long. I didn't think it was possible to find wings that small!! Called back and complained and they said they would bring me out a new batch as long as I gave them back the old batch, which I thought was kind of weird. IDK how they managed it but the second batch was actually smaller than the first. I almost thought they brought me boneless wings instead of regular wings. I called back and asked the kid behind the counter to give the owner my name and number and have he or she call me. No one ever bothered to call, so deuces Pat's!!  There's a A TON of other places to order from.

I went to Applebee's to watch an NBA Playoffs game and enjoy a couple of beers and cheap appetizers. 
First of all, they didn't have the game on television.  In fact, during the later part of the dinner rush, they didn't have any games on tv, just SportsCenter on every television set throughout the bar.  When I asked the bartender if she could put the game on, she seemed put off, as if changing the channel wasn't her job.  I waited approximately 15 minutes for her to figure out how to tune to TNT.
My second issue is that as I walked in, I noticed a sign advertising free mozzarella sticks if I wasn't offered a Corona or Margarita.  Of course, the bartender did not offer either a Corona or Margarita.  When I asked her about it, I was told that this promotion didn't work at the bar, as there were no signs at the bar, but there were signs at every table.  Seems like false advertising to me.  When I left, I looked at the sign again, and it did not state anything about having to sit at a table to be eligible.  As far as I'm concerned, Applebee's owes me mozzarella sticks.
That said, the beers were ice cold and very refreshing.  I ordered an Appetizer Sampler for food, which included boneless wings, spinach-artichoke dip with tortilla chips, mozzarella sticks, and some quesadillas.  All of which were quite tasty.  Also, the hostess was seemingly very nice.  She kept smiling and held the door for me both entering and leaving.
HOSTESS - Kori
BARTENDER - Dawn

Look, people: it's a motel. What are you expecting? You get what you pay for, and for $74, you get a $74 motel. 

Our experience was a very clean room, friendly staff, and extremely comfortable beds. We booked via Expedia with no issues. Only slight gripe is the breakfast room isn't all that great. But again: you get what you pay for. 

Would stay here again. 

+ across street from Busch Gardens
+ close to every type of food imaginable
+ close to Yuengling tasting room
- breakfast is pretty lame
- outdoor access to all rooms
- parking lot is small for the size of this motel

I've been here a couple of times and have always enjoyed myself. I'll admit that I'm reviewing Wheelhouse based on what it is and not what I want it to be. This a bar first with a fun chill environment where people gather to drink heavily. The food's decent, the drinks are decent, but the crowd is why you're here!
I came for brunch and the bottomless mimosas are a great deal and the bartenders were very attentive. I ordered the veggie omelet and a steak and it came out just as I expected. I had fun interacting and catching up with people, while getting to make some new friends. The drinks kept coming and I left happy. But I also understand what this place is, and I absolutely appreciate it!
Would definitely come back, and I'm looking forward to it.

We came to the Sunday Gospel Brunch last week.  It was an exceptional morning.  The buffet was done very well and the food selection was perfect.  All that being said, nothing could compare to the Gospel Show.  It was the most spiritual, sole revival, foot stomping/clapping event I have been to.  This is a must see when you are in New Orleans.  It beats all other Brunches in town.

One of the best brunches I have had! Really awesome atmosphere and amazing food. Very trendy and so many options for any meal of the day.
