Would give this place 5 stars 100% for great food and service, but the hostess at the front was very rude to one of our party members. We were seated while she was in the bathroom and she told her we hadn't been seated and must have left without her... lol. 

Overall would recommend to anyone in the area!

Hubby and I decided to pay visit to Quincy Street Bistro last night after discovering it through myTaste Card which we purchased thought St. Louis magazine blog. 

Upon arrival we were immediately greeted by a very friendly female hostess. Wonderful family atmosphere, great prices and overall incredible service. 

We ordered our drinks quickly and the food arrived shortly after. 

I order "The Mother-in-Law sandwich which was simply delicious. And Hubby ordered their Cajun Style Ramen with sweet chili. Both were fresh and were flavorful. 

We will definitely revisit Quincy Street. What's not to like the owner was one of the Finalist for the James Beard Award!
Maybe it was a one off but we didn't enjoy it at all. The salsa tasted like it came straight out of a jar and the food was extremely bland. Everything we ordered didn't come as described on the menu.
Food is okay the service was excellent, we went for my nephews birthday, the atmosphere in the restraint   has a Italian feel to it.

Standard corporate restaurant/bar/nightclub. Highly funded which means cool decor, lots of promotions and events going on, and a decently run business. It also entails mediocre food and service without the owner operator feel to it. Regardless its always a fun place to get tacos and drink margaritas, just drink , or dance. It's cheap compared to most places on state but so are the ingredients. Good place to go if you aren't trying to spend a lot of money or want to get drinks in a fun environment

We brought our 10 year old dog this evening  1/28/17, with a mayor ear infection (she was miserable and in pain). Bella was seen by Dr. H May.
The receptionist and check in was very nice and helpful. 

 But never have I been treated so rude and disrespectful by a veterinarian (Dr H May). Even had nerve to call  me stupid, said there was nothing wrong with my dog (I have 4 dogs and know if there something going on), wasting her time. Buy she didn't have any problem charging me $172 and proscribing 2 meds.  The clinic was not even busy. And then made us wait over 1 to get the medicine. 

Here is what the web site mission statement...

Your pet is more than just an animal - he or she is an important part of the family. At Veterinary Specialty and Emergency Care, we understand how special your companion is to you, and we're honored to partner with you in keeping them happy and healthy. With us, you'll get access to an elite team of doctors, specialists and support staff that are dedicated to making a positive impact in the lives of animals and their caretakers. More importantly, you'll get a team of professionals who are pet lovers first.
Whether your visit is for emergency medical care, internal medicine, rehabilitation, advanced diagnostic testing, laser therapy or something else, you can expect the highest level of care available, each and every time you visit. We specialize in offering premium services at an affordable price so you'll never have to worry about a thing! We're available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, 365 days a year to assist with all of your Southside & Greenwood area pet care needs. Give us a call today or stop in any time. Your Southside veterinarian would love to meet you!.

We were not treated with a positive experience. If you happen to get Dr. May, go to other provider. 

Will go elsewhere from now on.

This is a dive bar trapped in the 70's from whence it was formed and hasn't changed since.   That is actually pretty groovy as anything past the 90's sucks and is tainted with hipsters anyway.  They had great prices on their drinks and a nifty selection of brass name plates on the bar that have rather entertaining names on them.  They had a section for pool and darts and this place seems to be quite popular with the smokers.  I'm not a fan of smokers but this bar seemed less smokey than some of the others in the area.  I've also heard legends and rumors of a steak night on Thursdays with the infamous touring Metry lingerie ladies in attendance.  I actually know a guy that married one of those ladies.
Came in from Detroit needed a haircut for Valentine's Day.  They contacted and confirmed an appointment before they were even open for business.  Great service and great haircut.

I love this place! I especially love the chicken salad and rosemary roasters. My boyfriend loves their Pizza and all the great options like elk sausage. The only thing I've ordered her that I didn't especially like was the blackened chicken fingers.... they didn't taste much like chicken. Recommend the fantastic desserts, beer and staff.

My led was broke after a phone fall. They replaced my led on my samsung s5. Was $149.99.  To me a great deal especially since even with 5 people there I was out the door in less than an hour. Super people to deal with and a great service expierience. Thanks. They will have all my future business. Everyone of their employees answered my questions and were very professional.

The Hill thin-crust pizza is what I ordered (not a deep dish fan): the toppings were top notch, they don't massacre the pizza with that awkward Imo's style slicing, the crust is thin, crispy but oh so flavorless and bland. 
Good place for people watching though.

I used to go to Costco for all my tire needs but it is difficult to get an appointment there nowadays and Costco seems to also be continuously out of stock while they only sell high end pricey tires. I tried this place, I got a good deal online, they had plenty of tires in stock and overall I really liked it. They are very efficient.
We are BIG Central Pet fans!   Our corgi LOVES coming here for kenneling, daycare, and grooming.  The staff is consistently knowledgeable and friendly.

Great Motel in Santa Barbara!

We were there on a Sunday night, and you can't beat $89/night.  Loved checking out all the rooms on the website, as they each have a unique design.  We ended up in room 7 and it was great.  Room is very basic, but very clean!  There is a great little deck area with lounge chairs on the second level.  One note....Because it is an old motel, rooms 1-6 are on the first floor off the parking lot.

The staff of the Presido Motel were great.  All the rooms had a informational guide with staff restaurant/bar recommendations that were really helpful.  Best part of the motel, were the free bike rentals.  We loved spending the day pedaling around Santa Barbara.  The hotel's location on State Street made walking to restaurants at night really easy as well.

Can't wait to go back!  We already have our next trip booked!

This place is so good! Nice to have an addition to the restaurant near Harkins Theater! The waitress was great and the Mango Tango tequila drink was perfect (ask for patron tequila) and not too sweet.  The Skewers (appetizer) were very tender and delicious (steak, shrimp and chicken).   The grilled chicken dinner with the sides two sides was very good; rice pilaf was perfect and the macNcheese was creamy... but lacking something (not extremely flavorful), but good.  
The panko chicken sandwich was nice and crispy with tender juicy chicken inside.  I asked some chula sauce for an extra kick.  The seasoned fries were goos and had a more flavor seasoning than your standard seasoned fry.  The atmosphere inside was warm and inviting.  We also enjoyed people watching (all the folks coming and going from the Theater).  We would come here again!

I was in Reno for business when my tooth started hurting. I put off calling a dentist as long as I could because I hate going, never mind to a new dentist in another state. Finally the pain got the best of me and I called Modern Dentistry, based on their positive Yelp reviews. The office assistant, Mitsy, not only got me in right away but also made sure that my insurance went through correctly. I was able to see both the dentist and Endodontic specialist, who set a treatment plan. I have never written a review, but am so thankful to this dental office that I had to share my positive experience.

If you want Nashville hot chicken in St. Louis, then this is the place! The descriptions for their spice levels seem to err on the side of caution. Choose medium but will definitely get hot next time.

They never pickup the trash when they are supposed to. Its been a week and no trash pickup. One day they drove right by my house and never picked up anyones trash on the entire block. This company is horrible. When you call all you get is talking heads that accomplish nothing. Probably have had 20 missed pickups in the last 6 months. We need to get together and demand the city counsil that hired these buffoons to get another company! What are we paying for. Nest step is to find a number for corporate in Arizona. Their call centers are horrible and no help.

We were so sad when we couldn't get a reservation while we were visiting in Nashville. It looked like a fun tour. Luck was in our favor as there was a last min. cancellation and we were able to climb aboard the big pink bus on our last day there. The Jugg Sisters did not disappoint. I highly recommend you enjoy this tour if you love to laugh and have fun. BOOK early cuz they aren't kidding, it sells out quick!!! Thanks for the fun Sheri Lynn and Brenda Kay (you too Bubba!) from your California friends Keith, Shawn and Lori
What a menu! 86 west has a large menu that's I'm still working through but the highlight has been the fresh oysters paired with a delicious mignonette and classic horseradish and cocktail sauce.

while the reasons for meeting here were top notch, and the people who work here are as well, I cannot give four cause I can out cook this place at home.   there wasn't anything I tasted at this table that would bring me to come here again.    just standard.     the shrimp remolaude was so so.    by bbq shrimp was so so.   the gnocchi was tasty, but wasn't impressed with what was in it.   even my desert wasn't anything special.  the brisket which I was told is impeccable, was just brisket.

I waited for years to come here, and glad I did.  it is one of those places but don't expect to have a conversation you can hear.   LOUD loud loud.   drinks were great, and dirt cheap.   we were seated probably about an hour to hour and half later than our reservation.   I get it.  your busy.  its a sat night, but I was sheets to the wind from drinking my dinner.   usually this makes dinner taste better.  don't worry about salting your food, cause they def got that down.

I'd say my fave part of the entire experience was drinking it.   LOL

our party was fun.  loved everything about that.    huge table filled with fun folks celebrating, but I think the next big party that says to come here, I'll pass.

congratulations on being the second oldest restaurant in new orleans.  truly a thing.

I've never had issues with this location.  I'm constantly doing small projects that require random hardware, paint, etc.  I will admit, I rarely ever ask for help, and actually don't want to be bothered by people asking me if I need help, so my view on this is probably a little skewed.  

I usually stop by this Home Depot if I am on the way to Costco.  I always have some sort of project going and I am relatively absent minded and will usually forget something when I go to Ace.  

This location is organized, I can find help if I need it and usually has a good amount of checkout lanes going.  All in all it is okay.
20 visits I'm hooked.  The food is good, great service, ambiance is awesome!  The lunch special is a great deal!  chop salad highly recommended.
Stopped in and got some street tacos. The food was amazing! Had carnitas and carne asada. Will definitely stop back in when I'm in the area.

My family loves this place and the burgers and salad are delicious. My only complaint is dark meat chicken is used for the pitas. I'm picky as heck so I won't be ordering this here. The service is always excellent and the associates working there are super sweet and accommodating.

We both had to pay to get in as a couple. Lap dance was 40 bucks for one song and she didn't even let me be in the same room. Didn't have any fun there for my boyfriends Bday. Even though it's somewhat nice inside. Pick another place.

We always have a great experience here!

If you are a condiment whore like us then you will love this place. They have so many great sauces to choose from!

We loved the spicy chicken fried ravioli.

Also highly recommend The Pogue Mahoney burger.

Thanks for a great lunch!
excellent!!!!!!   consistent, friendly, great ambiance, fantastic happy hour.  amazing staff!!!!! thank you!

First time here- will DEFINITELY be back! Some of the best barbecue in the city. Had the pulled pork plate with mac and cheese and cole slaw and my girlfriend had the half rack of ribs with green beans and baked beans. Everything was delicious, perfectly smoked, the sauces were the ideal compliment to a wonderful meal. Have to go back to try the potato salad which is apparently a hit since it was Saturday and they ran out as well as the brisket and burnt ends. Quick, personable, and efficient service. Overall the perfect meal. It honestly could not have been better. Great job SMOKED!

90% of the people in line for Dinics were talking about Man vs. Food, so that tells you two things:

1) this place attracts tons of tourists
2) only 10% of the people could possibly be regulars (or maybe they just love Man vs. Food so much that they can talk about it for 30 mins straight)

"Adam Richman came more than two years ago."  I have that statement looping in the back of my mind as I write, because the guy behind the counter had it as the answer to the questions that were asked of him several times as I waited in line.

Of course, the reason I was in line (and in Reading Terminal Market at all) was because I saw the Man vs. Food episode.  So how was Dinics?  It was okay.  The pulled pork sandwich was fine, with a tender texture and somewhat flavorful meat, though it was more bland than I expected it to be.  The bread was a regular footlong, and the cost came out to $8.25 with tax.  That's decent.

Would I do it again?  No.  Not when Hershel's Deli is right across from Dinics, with almost no line, and with a heavenly pastrami sandwich.  And regardless of Hershel's, Dinic's sandwich is not worth waiting more than 10 minutes.  But, at least I can say I tried Dinics.

Speaking of that line, the reason the wait is so long has much more to do with the inefficiency of the workers versus the demand for the food.  They could fire half the staff and still have three people effectively chopping up the meat, putting it in the bun, and taking payment.
Absolutely the best place to go for pizza in New Hope. Definitely recommend getting the Sicilian pie.  Not as heavy as you may believe. Meatballs are very tasty. Great BYOB.

Place is a solid place to visit once a month or so. Food is either amazing or mediocre. I particularly like the smoked breaded Gouda- it's basically the best cheese stick in existence. It is a bit pricey for what it is, and they don't split checks which is irritating. Seriously, how hard is that to do?  Still a good spot just a little too douchey to go more than once every other week or so.

5 stars for service and food and mostly service. As Nashville is growing exponentially, their service is amazing. We go and my little person always has lots of questions and we over order. I look in the rear view mirror while he does this, so don't judge me if we take a little time. LIke I said, looking in the review mirror, I note if someone is coming. Luckly we have been blessed not to hold someone up. OK love love love love their coffee. Not bitter, not weak, perfect and price is right. Their soups seem a little salty, but not locally their fault, bc they are prepackaged. The bread is perfect everytime and the sandwiches are wonderful. We get the beef and asiago cheese often and love it. Not a fan of onions so we ask to 86 them. Also get the turkey sandwich and the bagels. Great deal 13 bagels and 2 smears for a great price. Again SERVICE SERVICE SERVICE. THEY ARE AMAZING. Tip! They are so amazing!

The Messy Tea is awesome!!! I would return alone for just for the tea. The nachos themselves were just ok. I ordered the nose runners and my husband had the ones with the shrimp, chicken, and beef. This was $34. The concept of the high end nachos was much better than the execution. The shrimp that was on the nachos tasted weird, like they were precooked frozen shrimp. However, I loved that they used D&D sausage on the nose runners. There was way more toppings on the nose runners than on the nachos my husband ordered. Also, they were very gentle with the amount of cheese on the nachos. I wish there was more cheese.

We went on a Monday around 1:30 pm. There was no wait nor no other customers in the store. So I'm assuming it was a slow business day. So we didnt experience a long wait.

Overall, the business is worth a visit if you want to try them out.
My family of five came here on Mother's Day and we had a wonderful meal and experience. The food was incredible! It came out right away and tasted amazing. We will definitely be coming back!

I walked right in after work and was helped promptly with a smile. The lovely woman who shaped my nails did exactly what I asked and check the shape with me. I've had many salons just kind of assume they know what shape I want or how long I want them to be. None of that here. They did a paraffin dip at the end and applied the polish so evenly. I will be back !!

I love everything about this restaurant! Their local seasonal menu, the ambiance, the food, the wine, the best bread pudding I have ever had and the friendly wait staff. Eating there was truly an experience for the senses - the food smells, looks and tastes good!
Went once, had a nice experience and the food was really good,that I'm looking them up now to place an order for pick up.
Extremely friendly staff, quick but thorough manicures and loved how close it is to my hotel (marriott courtyard down the street). Good quality for an even better price! And a gel is $30! Yay!
CLOSED.  Although with a 2.5 star average on Yelp and owner who seemed to let this place slide from marginal at opening to worse as time went on, I imagine it isn't going to surprise or upset many.
Great food!  Great service!  Rivals some of the top notch trendy cuisine I've encountered in Philadelphia, Manhattan, and Miami! I HIGHLY recommend it!

Delicious food, I had the macho salad and loved the taste and it comes with cornbread croutons!  We also had the honor burger that was also delicious.  Definitely coming back again next time I'm in Montecito.

Hands down best taco salad in the city. Regardless of the time of day (or night), I'm getting it if the kitchen is open. Usually close out the night here after a concert or post intramural volleyball game.

Best sandwiches I've ever had anywhere. I don't say the previous statement lightly. I'd put this place above Nardelli's in CT, Dalessandro's in Philly, etc.

The owners are unbelievably nice and always offer samples of their newest offerings. I'd eat here everyday if I could.
We have come here 2 times since the menu update. Food is fantastic, prices are fair, margaritas are a bit too sweet but still good. Great Mexican place for a date.

A very underrated pizza shop that is tucked away in a small strip mall in Marlton. It has got to be one of my favorite pizza places around South Jersey. It's a good place to stop in to get a quick slice of pizza when you're on the go or on a lunch break. I've had pizza here before and you can't go wrong with their pizza, especially the Grandmom pizza and chicken bacon ranch pizza. The service is really good and the servers/counter people are really nice and friendly. They do delivery as well, so I can order and get my food without having to leave the house. Definitely give this place a try!

Great breakfast place in the heart of french quarter. Simple, and very tasteful. The staff is super friendly. You might have the pleasure to hear one of their waitresses sing for you! Will come back next time I'm in NOLA!

Spectacular. Bubble tea and the sesame tofu are awesome.

They don't accept American Express -- Visa + Mastercard only.

Amazing! Great atmosphere, unusual but not bizarre menu. Escargot amazing.
Duck entrees delicious. Presentation before cheeses are selected was fun and informative. Cheeses were delectable.
Sides on entrees were skimpy but tasty  (if you could find them!)
Will definitely return

Food is always solid and service very attentive. There seem to be some inconsistencies in food preparation... Mainly the pizzas. I have had the same pizza (proscuitto) but made differently different times. Love the cheeses and how they are paired. Quail and pork chop are amazing. Overall a great spot for a good dinner.
Service isn't the MOST amazing, but I've never been upset. As for food, it's definitely worth a try. I love the lemon chicken and Vietnamese coffee is amazing!!

Considering how many people I've had recommend this sushi location, I must say I was disappointed in my experience. The waitress did a poor job of explaining how the ordering process works here.  Each time you would like to order, you fill out the sheet or else you will receive everything else right around the same time, even if you order a LOT of rolls for the table.  I had been lead to believe it would be staggered, though I will admit I may have just misunderstood.

I only really enjoyed two of the (again) MANY rolls that we tried.  They had many options with unique ingredients but I found that many tasted the same regardless of their contents.  Also, the menu is not clear on what is included with the AYCE.  The waitress didn't check in for long amounts of time and we had a very large waiting period between our two orders due to this.  My friend also requested a drink when he arrived and didn't get it until we reminded the waitress for a second time.

I'm unsure if this was a busy night with low staff or we just ended up with an unenthusiastic waitress but I'm not inclined to give this location a second chance. Not when there are multiple other sushi restaurants in the area offering the same AYCE deal.

Very simple restaurant. Home cooked food served pretty quick. The service is not what it was at the old location , probably because they have more customers now. The owner used to say hi to is Everytime now she just sits down and rings people out. But o really great food for the price.

I was craving Italian on a recent trip to Philly and my friend recommended Little Nonna's. I went for lunch and it was pretty busy so I recommend making a reservation online. I love how there is a 3 course lunch option for $20. I got the mushroom arancini, sausage rigatoni, and tiramisu. The arancini was crispy, hot, and oozing with yummy cheese and rice. The truffle flavor was delicious! My main course was great. The rigatoni with pink sauce was on point and had savory sausage pieces in it. The star of lunch had to be the tiramisu. It was so soft and fluffy and loaded with whipped cream and nuts. Probably some of the best tiramisu I've ever had. My dad got the meatball dish and the portion was gigantic! 2 giants meatballs served with a ton of pasta. I highly recommend this place because of the excellent service and food!

This was my first time at Wing Stop and they did not disappoint. The people behind the counter were patient with me as I waited for my friends to decide on what they wanted (I was ordering for them while they were someplace else). Those who are patient with others are wonderful people. But I guess patience can only go for so long, which is why I'm glad my friends didn't take forever to make up their mind. LOL

I got the hot boneless wings, and WOWOWOW. I LOVED THEM. Delicious and affordable. I am a huge fan of spicy food and this was nothing short of what I expected. In fact, the wings exceeded my expectations. Going to Buffalo Wild Wings set a standard for me because I've been there more than Wing Stop, but this place blew my mind the very first visit.

Their fries are awesome; I would order a bucket filled with them. That's how good they are. They also have a really neat soda machine. It's one of those new ones where it's an actual program designed for you to pick a certain beverage.

Please come here and support this establishment! Wouldn't be such a bad place to dine while watching the finals for the World Cup... WINK WINK
A recent transplant, I'm so relieved to find Philly-quality food in delco. Super delicious!

I hate to give such a disappointing review for Terra Sur, as I really had good expectations, but it just didn't turn out as well as I had hoped. The first time I came here was with a large group as part of a "meetup" group. I arrived at our agreed upon time of 630 pm and we had made a reservation for 18 people far ahead of time. Being that the restaurant is quite small we were split into 2 different tables. From the outside it doesn't look too impressive as its a small place tucked in at the end of a strip plaza, but inside it is very nicely decorated with an array of artwork covering the walls. Very cozy feel, which is nice, considering you're likely to be here for a LONG time.

 I'm not sure if it was due to the large size of our group but everything took far longer than it should have. We got water right away but no drinks menus until we asked for them at least 15 minutes later. They do have an extensive wine and beer list with libations from around the world, presuming you can get anyone to come take your drink order before you decide to just give up on it. Another 45 minutes later of sitting there staring into space before someone takes our appetizer order. Yes, 45 minutes! 5 minutes after we finally get a bread basket for the table. By the time they took our order I was so starving I decided to get just an app rather than wait to order a whole entrée in order to avoid waiting longer. 

I chose the tostones with seasoned minced beef, onion and red bell pepper on top. Luckily after all that waiting my app did come out quickly along with the Ceviche that others at our table ordered for their app. Those who ordered meals were stuck waiting for another extensive period of time. Sadly I wasn't all that impressed with my tostones. The menu description should read "large tostones cakes with tiny pieces of fatty beef on top, 1 sad little bell pepper slice and an ENTIRE large onion"  Seriously there was so much onion I could barely find my other food underneath. It was overkill. My first thought was that perhaps I just didn't order the "right" thing, and that's why I was disappointed, but then I thought "shouldn't anything on on the menu be a "right" thing to order?!" Meh. 

By this point I was over the whole experience and ready to get out of there. Due to the size of our group we were told they could only split our bill into 6 per table but I was able to flag down one of the servers, paid cash and skidaddled out of there. Not sure that I would go back again

Nice pool, nice golf course, great venue!

I've been here plenty of times and I am a fan. Their food is usually good, too. Not the best location, but where else could they put it?

I've been to several weddings here, and they definitely do a good job. Because the last wedding was so large, they had to use a lot of rooms which made it seem a little sectioned off. One of the rooms we were in was also used for a rehearsal dinner for another wedding.  They usually have good service, also.
Hate to say I forget her name but our hostess was very friendly, the wines some of our favorite - most were subtle easy going but just quality - will go back - did both red and white flights

Had a private party for my mother's 80th bday in one of the private rooms. Everything was great. It was easy to arrange and reasonably priced. Lots of options for appetizers and entrees. Private bar in the room we had. Attentive service and party went without a hitch.

I love this place the food is great. Love the delicious unusual pizzas. The only downside is the service is all high school and college students. They don't take there job very seriously. The place also really needs to be cleaned the tables are covered with crumbs and so is the floor. On the bright side they have this really awesome healthier soda, not any of the main stream brands they were really interesting and fun to try.

Glad they are friendly and having fun at work, but these kids play too much. Should have been in and out much quicker, but at least have the staff were just joking around (while what seemed like the new girl was left fending for herself on the line.)

We went later in the evening and there was a long line, so a lot of the menu was sold out. We tried the pulled pork and it was delicious! Prices were very reasonable, especially because of the large portion sizes. I would definitely eat here again.

Smells damp and slightly mildewy. The decor is almost painfully cheesey. The sound system is so outdated the bartender couldnt figure out how to get the music going. But I am all for this place. The beers are cheap. The service is friendly, funny, and sweet. It's been around for 30+ years so there is some good history there. When we walked in, we were the only guests in there. I mean seriously, we thought the place was closed because the lights were dimmed and it was absolutely quiet. I'm not complaining though. Sometimes it's nice to have a quiet beer with the person you came with. This is not a place for everyone, as the other reviews clearly attest to, but if you take it for what it is and aren't expecting the kind of drinks, food, or service you'd get at a five star joint, you won't be let down.

I just wanted to do some regular shopping, but was bombarded by employees who kept pointing at the beer and wine section.  Even the cashier pointed out that this beer was on sale and that wine is excellent.  I told the manager that it's not right to bombard customers with this type of stuff because some people don't drink.  They are also way too expensive. Give me a Giant anyday.

After making a last minute appointment, my daughter and I were welcomed as soon as we walked in. I had no idea that my gel fill would become an even better experience. I was offered a " color" powder dip. Reluctantly, I agreed to do it. All I can say is , wow. My nails look so natural and they feel light and healthy. Yvonne was very attentive to detail and the process was what I describe as " state of the art". My daughter swears she had the best pedicure and foot massage she ever had. I highly recommend this place and hope you will have an opportunity to get Yvonne herself. I will come come back next time I am in town. The prices were very reasonable, too.

This is a terrible McDonald's. The service is terrible. The managers done care. The employees curse and are extremely loud. The food is either burnt or wrong. It takes 20+ minutes for it to come out sometimes. Worse McDonald's in Chester county.

Is Pho Hoang going to re-open???

Thanks so much for:

Not putting a sign on your front door

Not posting your closure on Fb and Yelp

Not communicating with your customer base says so much about Pho Hoang!

I absolutely love this salon! It is very comfortable and welcoming. Dianna does my nails every three weeks. She is very talented and can do anything I ask for. I always bring in a picture of something I like on Pinterest and she makes my nails look better than the picture. I highly recommend going to Dianna for your nail needs, you won't be disappointed!

Their selection and prices are very good. However the service is pretty bad. The last few times I've gone there, multiple employees have acted like I am annoying them. I'm sorry I don't know where the vinyl tubing is (Not really though). Then I had to wait 10 + minutes for them to cut me a piece. I've heard more then one employee complain about their job right at the customer service desk. Ill probably try to stick to Home Depot.

The Blue Beach Café!   What does that mean?   Blue Beach?   Hmmmm sounds better in Spanish.   

Playa Azul is a Santa Barbara staple.  I can't remember when it wasn't around it has been so long!  So you would expect that Playa Azul would be kind of "old school" Mexican food, and when you look a the menu it kind of is.   They have a lot of the traditional combination plates like taco and enchilada with rice and beans or a chile relleno and burrito.   But they also have some wonderful stand alone dishes that would make anyone's mouth water.  

While I don't really think that they have the absolute best Mexican food in Santa Barbara they are certainly top tier.    While they don't have a salsa bar they do give you some very tasty salsa to go with your chips.   

I recommend their margarita as well!!  You don't have to go fancy, the house margarita is absolutely wonderful.     

One of the nice things of course is the great patio.   A great place to sit, sip and crunch a few chips.     

Certainly the only Mexican restaurants in this town that are better are some of the hole-in-the-wall places or are too busy to accommodate a group.  If you want Mexican food for an office party or a rehearsal dinner I would suggest that this place is absolutely your best bet.

3.5 stars to be exact. 

This bar harkens back to the days of old, when men were men and women were men. No frills, no pretension whatsoever. It's not a dive bar because it doesn't deliberately sink itself down to that level. Instead it's a local watering hole that serves good old fashion American food, deep fried to perfection. I hereby give this bar: one full stomach.

The Pho (with chicken) was delicious and fresh with sides of cilantro, mint and sprouts. We also had a spicy clay bowl, scrumptious spring rolls and Duong Chau Fried Rice.  The service was friendly and quick and the prices were good.  We can't wait to go back again (Westtown Location).

I really enjoyed the lunch buffet today at the Queen of Sheba. It's a relatively unassuming place, but I thought the food was well prepared and very tasty. They had many vegan options such as curry-like red lentils and yellow peas and other vegan options, as well. They also had one beef dish and two chicken dishes, along with the spongy bread, anjera, a mixed fresh salad/relish type dish, hot pepper sauce and a couple of other delicious condiment type things that I'm not really sure what they were. Tasted great, though! The combination of spices used in their dishes is really bold and flavorful. The lunch buffet is served on Thursdays and Fridays only, and the wait staff is very friendly and helpful in explaining the different dishes. I will definitely be back!

This place we ordered food for around sixty dollars but was not told u get a two dollar charge for to bring your food u have to pay two dollars . Then to come find out when u order some much food over I think it is 25 dollars u get a free dish but u must tell them p. So if you don't look at what u are paying plus I gave the deliver driver four dollars they have put such a bad tasty in my mouth when we went down there to talk to them about what they are pulling so sad
I ordered a gluten free vegan pizza and it was pretty good. the service was ok. The pizzas are personal size and one alone will fill you up.

In the midst of quarantine covid-19 pandemic, I managed to lock myself out of my house when attempting to go on a walk. Broad Ripple Lock Service came to my rescue! They arrived promptly. I was back in my house within 30 minutes of calling them.   I was actually still able to take my walk because they were so prompt. The price was also very reasonable. Would recommended if you find yourself in this situation.
The staff was supper friendly but the food was ok. Didn't really like the fettuccine just the shrimp in it. The soup was too salty but tasty. Olive Garden's fettuccine is much better!

How would I survive without my dear H mart?

I love grocery shopping, period. However, shopping at H mart is more than just shopping for the sake of restocking the refrigerator. I usually start from the fresh produce on the very right side of the market. Everything is very cost efficient compared to other(American) grocery stores. Also, the products are always oh so fresh. Both conditions are to be met at all times due to the major clientele base of H mart - Korean housewives/ mothers. They just know. How? Beats me. I find that H mart's mushrooms and broccoli selection is one of the freshest in town. 

If you like sauces you've had at some Asian restaurant, they most likely have it here. 

AND they have fresh pork belly(the-never-frozen kind!)

I frequent this place and if you haven't been there, I strongly urge you to go. One downer is that the parking lot is so impossible to get in & out...but that really doesn't stop me from going there.

PS: Try banana milk. So awesome! But it's on the pricier end - 8oz for a buck, I believe. :(

Thank you for all you do. I  appreciate your understanding during the pandemic.  Everyone needs to get along now. I only gave 4 stars, because sometimes the office staff is rude. Not the doctors or nurses,  just the staff.

I've been here a few times and always greatly enjoyed their soup (the only thing I've actually ordered). If you like spicy food (as you should if you're coming here), order the noodle soup with shaved noodles and definitely get the shaved noodles. They're fresh, a little chewy and fantastic. The marinated egg is also a delicious add-in. Just be aware that they are cash only and that they have an ATM if you need it. Cheers.

Three adults really appreciated the attentive service of our waiter and all of us enjoyed a delicious buffet.  Although a limited number of entrees we did enjoy the tandoori and butter chicken the best.

If you go to this place please make sure you ask a lot of question.  They scheduled my boyfriend for a procedure that required him to be under and I scheduled my day around to make sure I could pick him up when it was done so I wouldn't be sitting around for an hour and a half.  Well these bozos failed to mention that the driver of the patient had to be present before they could even start.  The appointment had to be rescheduled and so did my work schedule.  Thank you, you inconsiderate staff at Western Dental.
Awesome place, food is great, people are nice. Nice entertainment as well.

Basically giving two stars because it's cute inside and out of pity. Every time I go here it's such a disappointment! I just got home with my bagel and it's burnt, and has hardly any cream cheese on it. This is the FOURTH chance I have given this place, but I won't waste my money again. There are plenty of better bagel places around and I would recommend taking your business there. There's also no reason to wrap a bagel with cream cheese in foil- it's wasteful. I worked at a bagel joint for 3 years- just wrap it in paper.

Let me start out by saying Nicck is the only person i will ever let touch my brows again. I starting seeing him a short 3/ 4 months ago and cant even express the change in my brow shape already. He doesnt just tweeze or wax your brows, he shapes them and takes his time with every customer. And i dont just love him for the work he does, he's an amazing person as well, so sweet, and very friendly. I promise you wont ever be disappointed when you leave his salon.

Quite possibly the worst dining experience I've had. We were in town for a conference for a week. The conference is the LARGEST fire department training conference in the WORLD! They had 2 waitresses. We never saw our original waitress more than the drink order which was delivered by someone else. The manager, who made it known she'd been at work over 12 hours, ended up delivering our drink order 45 minutes after we ordered them. Ordered apps which never came. The tacos we ordered came over an hour after the order was placed. The tacos came with chips and salsa and fries. At the end of the ordeal the second waitress told us they weren't going to charge us for the chips and salsa........which was good because THEY CAME WITH THE MEAL! Boo on Tilted Kilt. Time to go back to Undercover Boss because the first time didn't work.
Amazing Lebanese food. Best I have had in years!  Owners are great and make feel very welcome. This is an amazing find and my new favorite.
They have the best crabs...a little pricey but good. The place is always packed so be prepared to wait a little if you go during peak times especially the weekends.

Stopped by for breakfast after a run on Davis Islands. It was good. Small place with a diner feel. Places to sit outside, which lots of people do with their dogs. Food was decent, eggs, pancakes, bacon, but not fabulous. Service was slow. They were busy when we walked in but by the time we were leaving the service still hadn't speed up much. My friend commented about all the dirty tables which I probably wouldn't have noticed otherwise. About half the tables were dirty/full of food and plates. That kind of turned me off. If I went back, I would stick to the eggs, home fries, etc. Pancakes were blah. On the spongy side and flavorless. Prices are good and everyone was very friendly. A nice neighborhood vibe.

This little stand was such a great lunch spot! I had two pupusas and a drink for about $10 which was more than enough for lunch. I had La Mixta and something else, I can't remember. They were both simple and tasty. People at the window were super nice. He handed me a sample of their special drink...it had a lot of different things in it that I don't remember (tasted like some sorta milk...it was yummy). Can't wait to go back and try other things on their menu!
Horrible customer service here. The cashier was rude, didn't care to tell me how I could get my Amazon discount and seemed pissed overall with life. I've seen better service at Acme.

Pardon the essay, but I had to get this out.

Ok, so I made an appointment, as recommended on their website. The place was already very busy, but I was immediately introduced to a "stylist" and taken back to the dresses. Yay.  I was looking for a formal evening gown for a red  carpet event and had printed out several pictures from their website to give an idea of what I was looking for. She didn't even glance at them and proceeded to tell me that my budget ($300 or less) restricted me to clearance dresses only. I was thrown by this since many of the dresses I saw on their website were listed at $250. When I said as much, I received an exasperated eye roll and was told that they don't carry anything that "cheap". THEN TAKE THAT OFF YOUR WEBSITE!!!! I became even more frustrated when it became clear that not only were the prices wrong, but the website leads you to believe that they have a huge selection of styles and colors, when that is not at all the case. 
We managed to find 3 dresses for me to try on and then we went to the dressing rooms. First of all, they literally have a timer outside each room and they time you. If I could pick one word to describe my appointment, it would be "rushed". I was rushed to pick out dresses, then rushed to try them on. I swear I got to spend all of 1 minute looking at myself in a dress before I was hurried along to take it off and move on to the next. You will be required to wear gloves. They state this on the site, but it's still annoying. Also, they won't let you take any pictures. WTH? I had to go shopping alone but I needed a second opinion. Pretty much impossible when you aren't allowed to get a picture. The third dress I tried on was actually great, I loved the color, the fit, almost everything about it. There was something wonky with one of the bra pads sewn in so I asked about fixing it. At first, there was no seamstress that could talk to me. When one did show up, she wasn't able to tell me whether or not she could fix it. I didn't want to spend hundreds of dollars on a dress that might be unwearable. No one seemed to care, because at this point I was told "it's already on sale, there is nothing we can do" (which came across as "either buy the dress or get out, you're wasting our time". Apparently they couldn't care less about selling you a quality product. 

In the end, I walked out without a dress. In a way, I was glad that I didn't have to give them my hard earned money after the, shall we say, underwhelming customer service I experienced.

I am very surprised to be the first person reviewing this fantastic restaurant.  As such I will try something more detailed than my normal reviews.

Firstly this is not really an Indian restaurant and it definitely is not a South African restaurant.  It is Indian food that comes from South Africa.  This may seem a subtle difference, but if you are either you will notice right away.  Indians who migrated to Africa (I am one), could not find their normal ingredients to create typical dishes and thus a fusion came about using local ingredients and Indian cooking techniques.  In most of Africa this resulted in a milder and more subtle flavors.

The decor is very nice and open, perfect for large groups and families.  This is a family run business and you will definitely meet them at some point in the evening.  They are charming and quite happy to chat and answer all your questions.

This is a buffet, but to it's credit it has something for everyone and makes it perfect to try many new things.  They claim everything is organic and free range and thus the moderately high price (25$).  The quality is evident and I considered it good value.  The food itself is good, in a buffet you will have the hits and the misses and this was no exception, but I found enough that I liked to be satisfied.

Having spent 6 weeks in South Africa last year, I was hoping for a couple of dishes or at least wines that could take me back to that wonderful country but unfortunately this was not the case.  They mentioned they were trying for a better South African wine selection, but it would take some time.

Overall a good restaurant, perfect if you want to try,or introduce someone to a milder less spicy Indian cuisine.

I've been a customer in pharmacy since September 2013 since CVS screwed up my wife's rx the clerk was unprofessional seemed like she didn't care the next day I transferred my prescriptions to Riteaid carp my wife also transferred her and her moms prescriptions I've been happy ever since I transferred to them staff always friendly helpful good humored now all 3 of us have ours there conveniently.
My sister and I (we're 21 and 25) came here for a Halloween party and we had a fun time. There was a ton of dancing. Drinks were way too strong, but I guess that could be a good thing to some.

My favorite food truck, not just in Indy but in any city I've ever visited.

I eagerly look forward to every Wednesday when they come over to my part of downtown for lunch. Eating here just makes you feel flat out *good* ... how many places can you say that about?

Sometimes I get the vegetarian option, sometimes I don't.  Either way, you can't go wrong.  Whether they have veggie Reubens, real meat gyros, tofu bahn mi, or a prosciutto & mozzarella sandwich, you can be sure that it'll be utterly amazing.  Fresh, balanced flavors unlike anywhere else in town.  Service is super fast and friendly too.

To top it all, the desserts from Duos are quite possibly the best in Indianapolis.  Tremendously rich and decadent ... very difficult to resist once you've tasted how crazy flavorful they are.

Finally made it back here to give it another shot and with it's expanded hours it made it easier.  

The staff were wonderful as always, generous with samples of the soups (I didn't want to be greedy so I only tried 1 and asked for a recommendation between 2).  I sampled the albondigas (mexican meatball soup) but went with the chicken pot pie soup and a half turkey sandwich.  The turkey sandwich was huge, on soft fluffy cheese bread with moist thick slices of turkey.  I love the strawberry salad it comes with and of course the chewy warm cookie.  My friend loved her club sandwich and her chicken tortilla soup.  We both had lots of leftovers.

I still am not crazy about their soups, better than last time and I know they constantly try new things and tweak recipes to please their customers.  They still deserve top ranking for providing a much needed local dining spot with beautiful salads, sandwiches, and the best staff in town.  I'll be back more often and will bring friends from out of town so they know Reno isn't all trashy and casino diners and buffets.
I tried the risotto with scallops and it was AMAZING! I had never tried risotto before so I wasn't sure what to expect, but I was. It disappointed, it was so good.

We enjoyed our stay here.  Free parking, large rooms, full kitchen, beautiful courtyard and roof top deck were positives for us.  We thought the pool was tiny but worked perfect for our 8yo and 10yo.  Location is okay.  Gym is tiny, and needs some fans!

Strong 4.7!  Super cute decor!  I love this place. Lindsay, our waitress was very attentive.  We came straight from church and had tickets for a matinee so we needed quick service.  We didn't share this with our waitress because we didn't need to.  We ordered the deviled eggs and a steak salad to share.  Both were equally great.  We ordered our app and engaged in a conversation and didn't realize that our deviled eggs hadn't come, but we didn't have too.  The GM, Anthony, came to our table and apologized and advised he would comp the app for the delay.  Wow, what great service!!!!  True reflection of how a GM should be aware of the food and service on the floor at all times.  The steak salad was great. Lindsay brought the vinaigrette and the ranch on the side.  Ladies, the bathroom was impeccable.  Take home message: Excellent service, well seasoned food, friendly staff, beautiful decor.  A win!!!  You would be pleased to come here for a quick bite or a special anniversary dinner!!!

On Saturday, my boyfriend and I came in. We were waiting in the lobby for a table when we saw a roach. My boyfriend assured me it probably just came in from outside. We were seated at the sushi bar and ate a whole bunch. I ordered a bunch of mussels and they came out quickly. On my second set, there was a roach baked into one. I showed my server, where he just took the mussels, didn't say anything and left. Came back and said it was a crab. Obviously, we lost our appetites and wanted to leave. We sat there for 20 minutes not ordering anything and waiting. The extremely accommodating and nice sushi chef flagged down our server to give us our tab. He charged us for a lunch and dinner to compensate us for finding a pest in our food. I tracked down the manager, Jeff, and told him the brief dialog between the server and me, emphasizing that he tried to convince me this was a crab. He told me to not worry about the bill, but baby crabs look like just roaches.

My mom, grandma, and I walked in without an appointment, and we were promptly seated! The atmosphere, service, and price are great, and we were satisfied with our pedis! Great spot and great atmosphere!
I've lived in Tn and lived in Williamson county for 28 years and never even heard of them until we passed it.

I love this place for many reasons. Their wine is excellent! The menu is always changing with dishes that have seasonal vegetables from the farmers market. 

Having traveled to India a few times, I'd consider myself an Indian food snob.  I'd say hands down that Bibi Ji has the best Naan in Santa Barbara.  I eat there all the time and always leave full and happy.

We recently tried the Baingan Bharta which is my new favorite!

While the decor may be lacking, the service, food and drinks more than make up for it. The chicken nachos with wonton chips are killer and two can eat with leftovers. The White Russian drink is unique and better than any other we have tried. We started copying this drink and making it at home. The draft beer selection is crazy and comes with it's own menu. The service is where they really shine. The wait staff has never let us down and we always leave pleased. Ask for Gibby, he's the best but Rachel is a close second.

Aperitivo is truly a can't miss. It came highly recommended to my boyfriend and I from our friend, so we came on a Saturday night around 8pm. They don't take reservations, but we were luckily able to snag a table outside without any wait. Our waitress was extremely friendly and restaurant staff - including the owner - came out to greet us and make sure we were enjoying everything throughout. 

FOOD:
Everything was amazing. Each dish was brought out sequentially, which was really nice because everything stayed hot and there was enough time in between each dish for us to build up eager anticipation for the next! 

We ordered:
- Pesca bruschette: Oh my god. So so good. Our favorite of the night. Wish I took photos but I devoured it too quickly! Their bread comes from Oat Bakery next door, which has become my favorite bread bakery of all time. The bread was incredible - so soft on the inside but crunchy on the outside. It's covered with stracciatella, peach, sunflower seed and pine nut maple gremolata, basil and arugula. Perfect blend of savory and sweet and it was so light and refreshing. I'd go back for this every day if I could. 
- Porchetta bruschette: Also so good, though not quite as good as the pesca. The pork was incredibly flavorful. I couldn't taste the citrus flavor it says it has according to the menu, which could have elevated it to an even higher level, but it was very tasty anyways. 
- Gnocchetti with shrimp and pesto: Great pesto sauce. I liked the pasta a lot because it was pretty light, but it was cooked slightly too al dente for my personal preference. Shrimp was tender also. 
- Affogato: Quite possibly the best affogato I've ever had! I've normally only ever had affogato with vanilla ice cream, but the hazelnut ice cream with hazelnut crunch on the outside was insane. Soo good we had to slurp the last of the espresso with melted ice cream!

DRINK:
- Non-alcohol hugo spritzer: Very refreshing, loved the elderflower flavor and was really reasonably priced at $5! Appreciated the option for non-alcoholic on this one. 
- Aperitivo margarita: Awesome fruit flavors - I'm a sucker for both peach and passionfruit. They use a sake-based alcohol that tastes like tequila instead of actual tequila because they're a wine bar, and you can't tell at all. Would definitely recommend this drink!

When we walked in, there was no hostess and had to wait for a while to be seated. Then once seated, or waiter was extremely slow with every step - getting our order, drinks, and even longer to get our check. The food was also sub par but the thing that makes this a 2 Star rather than a 3 Star is the service. It was EXTREMELY slow in every way.

Amazing gelato! Every flavor I've tried is great. The affagato is also tops: espresso + gelato = yum! Super friendly staff, John and Miguel run a good operation. They also have coffee and espresso drinks. Highly recommend this place, a welcome addition to Haddonfield.

Not great customer service. I had my oil changed a couple months ago due to a loose oil plug as well as a tire leak. As I walked in to the store the kid at the front desk "greeted" me with a "what do you want?" On top of that it took them over an hour to rectify my needs. Other customers showed up after me and left before me(it was not that busy, there was an average of 2-3 other people in the lounge the entire visit). Some of the worst customer service I've experienced in quite some time.

Regular menu items are relatively expensive, so we had the lunch specials, which were $7 each (still pricey for a small portion of pho). We had vermicelli with chicken, rice with pork, and pho beef. Overall, the food was ok, but definitely not as good as our favorite places back home in San Diego. Appetizers and side-soups that came with the lunch specials were typical americanized Chinese style, and not good.

I love Riverwards Produce so much!  Store is laid out wonderfully, prices are great and they turned me onto some new tortilla chips that I now crave.  Staff was great and the music was on point for a produce shop.  Will def be back.

Always a great spot to stop in. I always attempt to make a stop by every trip to reno. This time we went for a batchelor party and brought the whole gang in. Great bar food. Great drinks great prices.  Its nothing fancy. But that's part of being a local bar. Makes you feel a little at home while being out of town and not knowing anyone!

Went there for dinner Sunday evening. Had the trio gumbo, red beans rice, étouffée. They tasted ok. Lots of rice in the small bowls. The waiter and staff were great. But an hour after eating dinner, I got sick and it all came back out... yuck!  Could be food poisoning. Not sure. But I wouldn't go back. :(

This place is honestly so much better than the rating. And that little picture of the tiny bug has been there for like six years... I've never had a problem, the food is always good, and it's delivered fast.

Where do I start.... we arrived at 6:23 we where seated right away then it went down hill. It was 30 mins for anyone to take our drink order and food order.  FYI it wasn't busy it was a Tuesday with lot of tables available.  We received our food about another 30 mins..... order the Ribs which were beautifully plated but dry and tuff also ordered the Whodat pizza which was ok but the crust was not cooked thoroughly .  On a brighter note the fries were good!  The place very nice but the service sucks.
Typical food for a diner. Doesn't blow you away but you get a quick decent meal.
Got a couple of their different tuna rolls and they were both a couple of the best tuna rolls I'd ever have. Would definitely go back if I were to ever visit New Orleans again.

Was gonna go to crabby larry's, then saw tu casa next door and a random mexican pang came over us.

Makes the best of it's relative small spice in terms of seating.  It is basically a square with tables against both walls and then down the center.  You have a view of the counter and kitchen in the back.  Definitely super casual.

The server promptly serves chips with salsa, however, the chips were topped with refried beans and cotija cheese - nice touch.  I'm sure if we wanted plain chips it wouldn't have been an issue.  Salsa was fresh made and very good.  Off to a good start.

We started with the puputas - corn masa stuffed with cheese and pork (there also is a bean option).  I love masa and pork, but for some reason I didn't love these.  The texture was chewier than expected, and the pork had an overly smoked taste.  Others seemed to enjoy it however.  

After chips with beans, and the puputas, I really was not that hungry so ordered one chorizo and one carne asada taco.  They did not come with any vegetables on the side, which really was fine with me, but if you're used to eating tacos at most restaurants you may be confused.  The chorizo and carne asada were absolutely delicious.  The quality of the carne asada here could be served in a fancy pants plate with a jose garces sticker slapped on it and you could sell it for 4 times the price.

My buddy ordered the shrimp fajitas, they looked, stunning.  You could tell how fresh it was and the shrimp were large.  Much better than any fajitas I've seen in recent memory, and my buddy vouched for its taste as well.

I'm pretty impressed with this place.  They do have a legitimate full hoagie shop menu including fried apps, cheesesteaks, hoagies, wraps etc if you happen to have a member of your group who would rather have a turkey wrap than a spicy chorizo taco.

Also - its BYO and they deliver.  I hope they stay in business!

Uncle Nicks has the best pizza I have ever tasted!! Not only is the pizza delicious, but the other things I've tried on the menu are great too. When I go in, the vibe is very inviting and the counter girl is extremely sweet. Don't just take my word for it, go find out for yourself. I cam guarantee you won't be disappointed!

It goes without saying that buying a home is one of the biggest decisions in life.  My wife and I just got married and are planning to start a family, so we were looking for a large enough house in a good school catchment and a fun but safe and family-oriented neighborhood, within our budget, AND with high ceilings (I'm 6'8"). We were looking for a house we could see ourselves in for at least ten years. No small feat in the highly competitive and fast-moving real estate market environment that Philly is right now.  We couldn't have done this without Paul.

Paul was extremely patient with us from the beginning. We looked at dozens of houses slowly finetuning our needs and wants, which for my wife and I were quite different in certain areas at the start. While we were looking at houses Paul shared just the right amount of information on value, immediate neighborhood and his opinion on how each house could be improved. There was no pressure applied on his part; he did a really good job of staying unbiased and open minded. He never discouraged us from looking at any particular house. I think he really gets the decision-making process people go through to find what they are looking for and understands the Philly market well.

When we finally decided upon a house, Paul guided us through a relatively stress-free offer, negotiation, and settlement process. We decided to "jump on" our house after only seeing it once, and given how fast homes are selling in Philly, we felt the need to act quickly. Paul made sure our offer got in at the end of a long workday, and we were under contract before the first weekend when apparently a mass of showings had been scheduled. Once we were under contract, Paul brilliantly negotiated a seller's credit that was significantly higher than we expected. We asked him how he did it, and he said simply that negotiation is his favorite part of the job. There were no hiccups while under contract at all, and Paul and the fantastic mortgage broker he recommended (Adam Funck of Annie Mac) were well ahead of any potential delay or missing information. Closing was a breeze, and we were in our new house before we knew it.

Paul is smart, experienced, professional, good humored and was a pleasure to be around during what can be a stressful process. While house-hunting, my wife and I heard several stories from frustrated buyers who lost out on favorite homes because of mistakes or missteps made by realtors or mortgage brokers, so we feel extremely fortunate to have worked with Paul. I would highly recommend him as a realtor and I plan to work with him again soon on finding an investment property.

Finally, a good Mexican place in Belleville!  after moving here recently, I thought I was going to have to make the trip to Fairmont City to get good food.  Tacos are delicious (even the green salsa, which I normally dislike).  The fajitas are huge and very tasty also.  The real star for me is the arroz con pollo.  Lots of chicken, onions, and peppers over rice and cheese.  Served with tortillas, it's amazing on a cold winter night.  

I like  the chips and salsa, not sure why some people complain about them.  Chips are a little thicker than some but are always hot and fresh.  The salsa is flavorful without being hot.  The flan is also consistently good and never tastes like it's been frozen for a month.

Service is generally excellent.  They do get busy and only have a couple of servers so you might wait a few minutes to get a table.  It's worth it.

My only wish is that they offered goat and tongue tacos!

Feels like a "big box" restaurant. It was heavy on gimmicks (crazy decanter contraption) and light on quality. Sashimi tasted as if it had been frozen. Prime sirloin was tough. I did love the French fries although they could have been hotter (maybe I'm too picky). 

Our waitress was great and the wine was good but if you're looking for an intimate wine bar with good food, this isn't it.

We were fortunate to find a parking spot on a street nearby after just one pass. With how late we started our day, we and other groups ended up waiting down the street at another establishment until the seating host radioed in that our table was ready. Loved the warmth of the sun through the window at my back.

Fried green tomatoes were recommended by one of the bartenders from the night before, so John and I ordered a plate to share around the table. Even our resident anti-tomatoite Kevin found them unoffensive, since they tasted like the fried batter more than the tomatoes themselves. The bed of unwilted organic salad greens served to help drain the residual fryer grease.

The others were content with their food: Julie's two eggs over easy with a biscuit, Ginny's breakfast quesadilla with tofu instead of ham, John's three egg omelet with chorizo, tomato, and cheddar, and Kevin's two giant buttermilk pancakes with bananas and peanut butter chips, plus turkey bacon. I was most jealous of Kevin's plate, largely from my astonishment that each pancake was the size of my head. Thankfully they took it easy on the powdered sugar.

Multiple latkes were ordered and I personally found them just shy of inedible. Potato dominated in texture, and the overall flavor was overwhelmed by the oil they were fried in. I generally enjoy a nice crunchy crust, but I felt that our batch was a bit too aggressively browned. I tried swiping it through the country gravy to improve the taste but eventually gave up on my latke. On the other hand I had no complaints about the full-sized PoBoy. The gently finessed chorizo omelette was folded into thirds. Instead of the traditional fixings, it's topped with a healthy ladling of creamy country gravy. I'm glad they saw fit to toast the open faces of the baguettes, since it kept the bread from getting overly soggy after inevitable gravy exposure. I also knife-and-forked this into manageable handling portions, but was ultimately defeated by the sheer volume of food in front of me.

Three and a half stars. Service was friendly enough, though we had to flag them down by hand for beverage refills once we got our food. Bathrooms acceptably clean. Cash only but the ATM in the corner makes it convenient for the easily forgetful. Cozy diner feel matches the homey food. I feel like this was the Roscoe's of Philly for me. I listened to too much of the hype and ended up with the impression that it was only okay. The food portions are ridiculous, but nothing about my brunch here blew my mind. Clearly I should've gotten the recommended French toast, or Jeb's open-faced biscuit sandwich. Even the burgers I eyeballed at other tables looked tasty. I'd be open coming back here to eat through more of the menu.

The red flags should have been blaring in my face; hindsight is 20/20.  Justin Brown contacted me (red flag) and stated the employees at Thoughtful Moving are all ex-military & a portion of the proceeds goes to 50 Legs. I thought, "How wonderful!" He asked me the contents of my home, but kept interrupting; he clearly wasn't listening & was just anxious to get the sale finalized (red flag). I have one king-sized bed, a dining room table with six chairs, sofa with two chairs, 3 TVs, a few misc. small tables &  usual boxes of contents from kitchen & bath, plus two suitcases of clothes. I also stated the washer and dryer were to go. Justin assured me this was an easy move and "worst-case scenario"--his words--would be 5 hours at $125/hour (to Miguel Burgos, owner: please share the recorded message, as you have stated in other poor reviews is available.)  Upon arrival on the day of the move around 9:00am, I should've been alarmed seeing the next red flag--a Budget rental truck. The two employees could not have been nicer, BUT NOT EX-MILITARY! They asked to see the contents at which time they said, "Well, this is going to be more than the quote. The sales guys give the quotes & don't really know. They don't care, they get paid on commission." - something along those lines. I am beginning to have enough red flags to start a marching band, but still on the stupid-wagon, I said, "That's okay, it is what it is," thinking it might be $100 more or so, never more than double!  They also stated that the credit card machine was down & payment must be by cash, Venmo or Zelle & due when they got to the destination before unloading the truck. I was alone on move day, so when they were just about done moving everything out of the condo & getting it on the truck, I asked if it would be good for me to go to the destination to get ready for their arrival. They jumped on that  (umm, yes, I know -- red flag)!  I waited over an hour for them to arrive--about a 20-25 minute drive. They clearly took their time--hourly work, after all. They finally arrived  after 2:00pm & told me $993 was due , on top of the $135 deposit. If I didn't pay, they wouldn't unload the truck.  At 5:40, when they still had most of my belongings on the truck or spread out on the driveway blocking three neighbors' garages, they said, "We don't get paid past 5:00pm," & wanted more money! I guess it took all the above red flags to finally knock me over. I asked to speak to their boss. They claimed they couldn't reach him, but got Frank, another boss. Frank listened to my complaint, answering, "I'm just a dispatcher," and hung up. I have a broken, crystal bowl, the TVs looked like a toddler got at them with a lollipop, they washer/dryer were left at the original location, so I had to get someone else to move those -- the list of issues goes on and on. PLEASE DO NOT USE THIS COMPANY!!!! SCAM from the word go! I still have items in my garage that weren't brought to my new place. Nightmare!

I'm unsure why it has taken me all of these years to write a review of dba... but no matter, it is, hands down, my favorite place on Frenchmen street.  Long before the "renaissance" of Frenchmen, dba was pouring excellent drinks, providing a great listening room for great music.   I think that dba offers a "grown-up" environment that avoids stuffiness and rebuffs the over-served bourbon street crowd while paying equal attention to music (if you are a chatting f*^kwit you're not welcome at some shows and will be asked to keep it down) and what they pour and how they pour it.

There are "two-ish" spaces here.  When you enter the right side is the main bar where people congregate until the music begins (or overflow when it is particularly crowded - which is often- in a good way). The left side of the building offers a continuation of the bar but features the stage for music and a dance area (or standing room when not a big dance night) to see the featured act.

Dance floor is filled for some sweet swing on some nights and packed on others to hear New Orleans' favorite bands.  Two shows on most nights and three on weekends - with music that ranges from swing to funk to brass and everything in between.  The early show often doesn't require a cover but a one drink minimum.  Later show averages $10 cover but a few bands are more.  

The staff is friendly, the vibe is decidedly Frenchmen with fabulous window seats to see all of the sights while taking in some fantastic music and sipping on a near perfect libation.

My neighbor recommended this place several years ago and we have been coming here ever since.   If you are looking for a decent, honest, competent mechanic this is your shop.  I have dealt with all kinds of mechanics over the years.  These guys have been the best to deal with.  Very upfront with you ; no up-charging; no up-selling ; no BS.    They have done everything for our from oil changes to exhaust work to brakes ; new tires ; inspections ; you name it, they did it.   Come here and you wont be disappointed.

I've been coming here for since they opened and I have never had a bad experience and the food is always so delicious and hot. This is where I would take people visiting from outside of Philadelphia because it's just that good.

This was the perfect spot for a salad after a big BBQ lunch! The options were all interesting. The base salad came in two sizes and the large were generous portions.  I got the Beets Me and my husband got the Smokehouse. We both added chicken and got dressing on the side. Great portion of chicken for only $2!!

For a salad called Beets Me, they skimped on the beets but I thoroughly enjoyed it! The citrus dressing wasn't super flavorful but both of the ones my husband got were delicious so i used those. 

The smokehouse came with pancetta, corn, and butter lettuce. The butter lettuce has a quite peppery taste if you're not used to it but it was good!

Overall, hit the spot and would def come back! The calzones looked amazing!
This was the loveliest subway I have ever visited. The employees were so warm and welcoming and genuinely friendly.

We stopped by while on a business trip.  Customer service was a bit sketchy at first.  We where not sure who our waiter was. They took a while to attend to us.  Finally management staff approached us to excuse poor service.  Food was superb will be taking my family to a location in Southern CA.
The staff was friendly and the killer bee wings were delicious. We had a nice time and would definitely go back!

El Camino might be the best thing that has happened to my life. The veggie wings make me insanely happy...I order them all the time.  My favorite servers and bartenders (Jill, Jamie, Regina, and Cracky) are always so friendly and make it so fun to be there.  They find time, even when their busy, to ask how my day is going and make sure I get home safe.  Good food and good people=El Camino!

We're so happy we chose Zeff Pediatric Dentistry. We recently took our 1.5 year old son for his first dental visit and couldn't be happier. The staff were very informative, and did everything they could to help our little guy be comfortable.

When I first called to set up the appointment, I wasn't paying attention to time and realized while I was on the phone that it was 2 minutes before they closed. I offered to call back during normal business hours and the receptionist insisted on helping me then. In addition to that, she even called me back later that evening to finish setting up the paperwork we'd need. I was very impressed, and appreciative of the great service.

The facility is the nicest dentist office I've ever been to, adult or pediatric. There are lots of fun activities for the little ones to do, and the office is open and well lit with large windows all over.

Dr. Zeff was knowledgeable and kind. She and her staff were great about the cleaning, and providing us with information and direction on how to best help our little guy be successful taking care of his baby teeth. 

We're looking forward to many more happy visits.

I'm about a week out from my visit to Setsun and I'm still thinking about it. We did a little bit of everything and I am so glad we did. There were a few items I didn't think I would like and I ended up loving them. Exhibit A: shaved cabbage. Sounds....gassy to a new mom who needs to feed her child. In reality, it was a take on a Caesar salad that was delightful and worth it. Exhibit B: white sweet potatoes. I didn't know there were white sweet potatoes and they were delicious as well. 

I keep thinking about the hamachi and oysters. They were standout dishes. The agnolotti delivered as advertised. Little cheesy pillows. I repeat, little cheesy pillows. 

The service was on point, the flavors interesting and execution was a 10. I will be back any chance I can get!
This is authentic Sonora Mexican food... my favorite.  The food has been consistent here for the 10 years I've been visiting and

Do not go to this restaurant.  Ordered gumbo which was more like a thin gruel with little chicken/rice/andouille.  On the menu it said Sweet Potato fries  $2.00 extra. Ordered that. Got the bill and it said $4.95 for regular fries PLUS $2.00 for substituted sweet potato!  Nowhere on the menu is it stated that sweet potato fries are $6.95.  The manager said "well, next to the sandwiches it said $2.00 extra."  In this place the customer is obviously not always right.  She did not even offer to give us the $4.95 price for the small plate of sweet potato fries that was standard.  Go to a REAL cajun food place.

Oracle Rd. location.  We've been taking out food from here for 15 years. We always order inside and always take-out a whole chicken with rice and beans. Originally the manager was always around to say "hi" and make sure everything was okay, but then he left and it was never the same again. I think that was about 7-8 years ago and we haven't seen a manager since. It went from a good meal years ago to very hit and miss and most of the time, it is a miss.  Most of the time the chicken was dry, so we started asking for one right off the grill which helped. The beans and rice are never the same two times in a row. The little salsa bar is getting pretty scary to eat from and most of the time it needs refilling.  After the Health Department cited them with multiple Violations, we stayed away for awhile.  We started going again thinking that it would be cleaner, better.  Tonight, we tried it again.  The salsa bar was half empty and a disgusting mess.  To make things worse, when we got home, there was no rice or beans in the bag. Called the place and asked for the manager and was told he had just gone home.  (Oh, yah, right!)  Explained what was wrong and was told to come back and get some. Seriously? It's rush hour and on a very busy street!  Asked for a credit and was told there was nothing they could do, but for me to come back and get them.  I guess that's a good thing because WE WILL NEVER GO BACK.

Lilette is a great romantic spot for young and old alike. I go here with my boyfriend a lot since we can always count on a great meal in a sultry atmosphere. The cocktails aren't really worth the price--too bitter for my taste and not enough liquor for the price. Stick with the wine because they have a great selection! 
We always order the raw fish special and it NEVER disappoints. Their moules (an app) are great in a delicious creamy broth that is big enough for a girl's entree if you're not trying to walk out with a food coma. The hearts of palm salad is fresh and light--just olive oil and shavings of parmesan is a clean, delicious dish. I also recommend the chicken soup--a simple chicken broth with fresh vegetables and a poached egg...a sophisticated twist on the classic. 
My boyfriend loves the juicy hangar steak served rare with Lilette's specialty fries on the side. and it's served with some bone marrow. YUM.
For dessert, they have an amazing chocolate hazelnut mousse which you have to have if you love chocolate and nutella. they sprinkle some fleur de sel on top which adds just the right amount of saltiness to bring out the sweetness in the chocolate. Or if you want something more light, Lilette always has a refreshing sorbet--our favorite is the basil grapefruit. 

Our only complaint is that the service is kind of iffy. Their servers aren't as attentive or polite as I wish they would be, especially Louis T., who is actually kind of an asshole.
