But one server isn't going to ruin it for us considering the food is just delish and is one of our favorite spots for birthdays, anniversaries, and romantic mid-week dates. It's right up there with the rest of our uptown favorites, Patois, La Petite Grocery, and Bistro Daisy.

It's still in a cavernous basement, and I still don't like the crowd it brings in as much as I like the crowd that Tattooed Mom's brings in. But I do have to say that it being non-smoking has improved Sugarmom's ten fold. you can actually enjoy a beer inside it without feeling your pupils burn.

Tattooed mom's does and will always have the better set up. But Sugarmom's will always have the better bumper car arrangement and air hockey. So I really do look forward to exploiting both facts more often!
Excellent service and food. This is one of my favorite Italian spots.  Bring a bottle of wine and enjoy.

This is an 'affordable swank' restaurant run by the proprietors of Dizengoff and other well-regarded Middle Eastern restaurants throughout Philadelphia. You can pick up some business cards for all of them -- and get up to speed on the empire's holdings -- at the host/hostess's podium. Or give them to your kid and say they're just as good as baseball cards.

While you won't run up a shock 'heart attack' bill, Zahav's P2P isn't great. The large entrees are comparable to the typical appetizer or snack at other places, and you really have to order 3-5 to feel satisfied. Lamb/chicken kababs are definitely standouts, as is some fish that I can't remember the name of. Hummus is all right, but only a notch up from Sabra or typical things you get at "Trader Joes." I found the texture of the pita also confusing: some of it crispy thin cracker, some of it more naan-like.

Taken together, and factoring in the hype and the fact you come here to know whether or not you should BELIEVE THE HYPE (cf. Flavor Flav), I'm going with a 3. I've had better at hole in the walls in Jackson Heights or food carts, but left with $40 more in my pocket.

You come to MC3 for the truth.

Great place, great location.  The barbers are great and the marketing model is great too. Costs as much as going to a Hair Cuttery or similar place but you get ESPN at the barber chair, hot towel, massage and a great hair cut. Definitely recommended.

Absolutely love this place.  They have done 3 of my tattoos and several of my wife's.  We have referred several people here and all have expressed how much they love their tattoo and the experience. This is hands down the place tattoo shop in the area.  Their artists rival bigger shops in the big cities.  Love it.

Decided to try this bar on a Friday night with some girlfriends, after years of driving by. It's nicely set up how it has indoor, and outdoor seating (outdoor seating while still sitting at the bar)! Unfortunately, is was pouring rain all night when we went so we were inside. It was busy, fun vibe, however the music was too loud for our liking. Could barely talk to each other across the table. Service was great though, drinks a little weak !

Still some of the best Mediterranean food in St. Louis! The service is still wonderful & the food is amazing. If you still haven't tried Omar's yet, get yourself in the door! Sit down & enjoy something spectacular already!
Great place. Monica our bartender was great! Food was decent and reasonably priced. Great atmosphere and  I will be back just because of Monica.
The atmosphere is great. The service is outstanding. The drinks are strong and crafty. The food is absolutely amazing. Stop wasting time reading reviews and just go!

I got married at Brigalias on 10/19/19 and my wedding was an absolute dream come true. Booking Brigalias was easily the best decision I made during my entire wedding planning process. From the moment I stepped in there during their open house in October 2017, I knew this was my venue. The chapel alone was enough to make me fall in love completely. From day one of booking, they were helpful with answering my many questions and the day of the wedding they went above and beyond to make sure everything was exactly how I wanted. This included literally last minute uplighting changes and centerpiece changes. They did it all without batting an eye. Diana is the sweetest person ever and is truly committed to designing your wedding exactly how you envision it. Jessica was our bridal attendant and I couldn't have been happier with her. She made sure we had everything we needed (even things we didn't know we would need LOL) She graciously handled my very energetic toddler during important parts of the reception where we couldn't keep our full attention on him. She was hands down AMAZING! Brigalias also took extra care of the head tables as well. The food was seriously amazing. I still have guests tell me to this day that my wedding was one of the best they have ever been to, and the amount of food during cocktail hour and dessert alone is no comparison to any other place. Seriously, the entire room was filled with dessert! I wish I got to enjoy it myself LOL. Not just the food, the new Grand Ballroom is to die for and I am so thankful I was able to have my reception in it. Brigalias knows exactly what they are doing and I now have photos and beautiful memories to last a lifetime. Thank you Brigalias for simply being the best! No other place compares!

Sandbar is a great place if you're looking to have a great time. We started off our night at the sandbar to celebrate my friends bachelorette! Max took care of us so well and helped make the night feel like a celebration! Definitely will be back!

P&K runs a pretty good happy hour from 4-6pm. The draft beers are interesting and when I went, featured at least two awesome local breweries (Tired Hands and Love City). They were just $4 a glass, though it is definitely smaller than a regular pour. The others in my group ordered sangria and cocktails and they were the most gorgeously presented drinks. There are good options for munchies including deviled eggs, cheese board, and brussels sprouts. The servers are very nice and accommodating. We sat outside and as an added bonus, got to pet and see many cute dogs out on their walks!

There are a few North Indian/Pakistani restaurants in the outer suburbs of New Orleans, and this one is the farthest of them, way out in Kenner (~1/2 hour from the city center). If you're there, this place seemed respectable. I received my takeout quickly (~10 minutes), and it was an eminently flavorful lentil dish with plenty of whole spices, and some samosas drowned in chickpeas and accoutrements.

I have to say I was mildly annoyed that their entrees come by default with naan. That being said, you can ask for rice instead. Also, the menu probably needs a rewrite just to be clearer to those people who don't know what all this stuff is.

All of this brings the place in just a tad below the other similar restaurant I tried and reviewed near the airport (at which I ordered the same thing for comparison). But I liked both of them and frankly, I haven't found anywhere in Orleans Parish where you can get this food for this price.

Pasteur is the place to go for good vietnamese food. The service is okay, but i have no complaints about the food. The soup for the pho is flavourful and the rice dishes are delightful. Will continue to come here for my vietnamese cravings!

Pats and Genos are both for toruists.  Real cheesesteaks dont have cheese wiz and are loaded with meat.  A step up is Johns Pork or Tony Lukes.  Both are a must try, but Johns Pork is the best for just about anything.  Also at Pats, you make sure your ready to order, and get it right, and have your money ready or the knock you off.  Not the best customer service, but they do try to keep things flowing.

Try Johns and update me what you think.

I went by their location on a Thursday to see about getting my dryer and washer repaired. I was told it couldn't be until the next Thursday. I called the next day and scheduled it for the next Thursday, and was told that Matt would call and give me a time window. I didn't hear anything Monday or Tuesday, so I went by on the way home and was told between noon and 2 on Thursday. (I took off work to be home.) At almost 2, I hadn't heard from anyone, so called and spoke with Dave, the owner. He was a jerk - said it was scheduled for the next Thursday and best he could do was sometime today. When I tried to tell him it was never scheduled for the next week, he was a real jerk - said did I want them to come or not. Of course I had no choice, I tried to speak and he cut me off. Said have a nice day and hung up on me. He then refused to answer calls from my number, and I had to have my neighbor call to find out if and when they were coming. The technician who finally showed up at about 4 did a good job, but I will never use them again!!!
I'm sad to change my review of this place. I like their product but I don't support their choice to discriminate to whom they serve. Time to find a new sweet treat destination.

No cable....room is nice...don't understand y the doors are locked at a certain time like it's rikers....the rooms are comfortable enough...front desk was helpful enough. They knew I wanted to b on the first floor but wanted to possibly smoke so they offered a room near the back door because the first floor was non smoking...that was cool. Breakfast is basic. Nothing hot. That's about it. It's just the rikers "lockdown" that I have a real problem with.

Before anyone says I'm biased for writing this review, get parts elsewhere and then come to Napa to for the right ones when the one you got doesn't fit or breaks. I am a mechanic and probably buy $500 to $1000 in parts a week from this store. Staff is super knowledgeable and get it right first time every time. There is nothing worse than working on a car on a Sunday afternoon and having to make 3 TRIPS to the parts store because they gave you the wrong seals twice in a row. That's right, I'm talking to you Auto Zone in Spanish Springs!!! If you need car parts in town, get them from Napa. You may be able to find them a few bucks cheaper elsewhere but trust me, you'll pay for it in the long run.
Dee gives the best haircut for men.  Will go back when she returns from sick leave.

Soup was luke-warm and tastes like it was from a can.  Friend's soup was cold - was supposed to be crab soup, but it was more vegetable soup with a few small pieces of crab thrown in.  Sandwiches were okay, but nothing I would rush back to have.  Two members of the waitstaff helped us and it still took a long time for food and drinks.  Doubt I would go back.

I have been going to this salon on and off for years for several reasons:

1. The pricing: in a town filled with overly expensive nail salons this one has always remained reasonably priced.  They also offer waxing services so to get a full grooming and girlie experience will run you anywhere from $40-$60 which is nice as I've paid double at other places.

2. The space: It's very peaceful in here and rarely packed.  I've reviewed papers for work while getting my nails done.  They offer wine.  Its a beautiful, clean space that is quiet.  I personally like the "nail bar"...great chance to socialize with new people or friends.  Win.

3.  The service: The technicians here are very helpful and are clear about what constitutes an upcharge.  

This is a hidden gem in the Nashville world of nail salons.  Every time I go someplace else and come back I am reminded that I shouldn't have strayed in the first place.

Just had the worst experience in Chipotle.    Walked in.   They were closing soon.   9:22.   Employees playing around, eating and yelling in the kitchen.    I refused to eat there and walked out after looking at the serving table.   If they're playing games in front of customers then they're more likely than not playing with the food.  
No one helped me or asked me anything.   No hello sir.  Nothing!

Where's the customer service these days? 
Ahh!    At Chick-fil-A!     Heading there now!

I'll bypass this location for sure next time!

I was so intrigued to check this place out but was greatly disappointed.  The lady has this lengthy introductory spiel about every room that is just overwhelming.  The racks and racks of clothes in the basement are grossly overpriced.  So is the furniture.  Basically the prices reflect that of a high end antique store although the lay out reflects that of a thrift store which she makes clear, it is not.  There is just way too much in there to even find anything.  I walked away with nothing.  Too much stuff, too much information and too high of prices!  She needs to reel it all in.

I always like to start my reviews with customer service then to the food. So that's what you will see here and then my overall reasoning of the rating.

With COVID-19 changing the way we not only live and disrupting our day to day routines it has affected our way communication. Many businesses and restaurants especially have relied on on-line and over the phone services lately and MSBC has done just that. However, I experienced some "technical difficulties" this morning whole trying to call in a to go order. 

The phone was left off the hook for some time. Approximately 30 minutes. Until then someone put the places the phone back on the hook and I was able to call. 

Once I finally got in touch with the restaurant the Front of house staff member answered very politely, friendly, and kindly which is always nice. However, the background was so loud I could hardly understand her and she could hardly understand me and naturally this caused a rough communication between us. But!! I understand she had little control over the diner being too loud. So I wasn't upset about it at all. If you do call however expect it to be kinda loud... when I picked up my order it was packed to the 50% seating rule and the chefs and back of house was clamoring to get what I think was a mass of to go orders (it was Memorial Day after all) 

When arriving the parking lot was easy to access and walking to the front door and inside everything was well lit, decorated and VERY clean! To say the least I felt more safe inside the restaurant than I did in my own home! All employees were wearing masks, enforcing the 6ft rule and maximum capacity rules strictly. I got my order and returned home. 

I ordered "the five" which was made of "Flaky biscuit, all natural fried chicken breast, pecanwood smoked bacon, a fried egg* and cheddar cheese topped with our house-made sausage gravy with a kick." 
1340 Calories LOL oh well it was Memorial Day lol all worth it. 

The food was packaged neatly and orderly. Still hot when I made the 10 minute drive back home. The flaky biscuit was drenched in their signature gravy, the chicken was well cooked and every bite was juicy and flavorful with perfectly seasoned chicken, melted cheese and crisp smoked bacon. 

This made me want to go to the mountains and sit on the balcony of a log cabin paired with their signature black coffee ! 

I give 4/5 stars due to the over the phone ordering system they have in place. It could use some work but they are just kids in the FOH it seemed like and everyone was professional and kind. Like I mentioned above the food was phenomenal but very very heavy and very greasy. This is not a factor in the rating however because it clearly stated what's in it and the calories so I willing ordered this with that in mind, just more of a heads up to someone else. 


I recommend MSBC and especially this location.
Women are harassed at this place and even after talking to security and management they do nothing about it! Worst place ever!!!!
Ordered a pizookie through bitesquad and it took them TWO hours to make it. They clearly don't care about customer service, you should care just as much about togo orders as dine in.

Cococo is the company that brought Alberta-based chocolatier Bernard Callebaut out of receivership. This new cafe is located just a block south of the former location, and is very spacious, selling chocolates, gelato, coffee drinks, and various dessert creations. The selection of gelato is quite good, although I was disappointed they were out of chocolate.

I went for an affogato with vanilla gelato. The espresso did not totally obliterate the tasty gelato, but there was still a lot to drink when I got to the bottom of the cup! Very refreshing on a hot afternoon.

Staff were very friendly and some of the desserts looked absolutely delectable. I will be back.
Cheese burger deluxe and fries were great for the price. Service friendly and speedy. I've been here several times and it's always consistent.
With everything that is going on I was able to get a great meal today while I had to make an emergency trip to the city. Great food! Thanks to the staff for keeping it alive

If you want to be videoed without your permission then come here!! Otherwise stay away!! If I could rate this establishment as zero stars I would but sadly yelp doesn't allow zero star reviews. I went out for a fun night with a friend and for the majority of the night we were having a great time. We came for the FBF back to the future nights and had a wonderful time bonding with the bar tending staff (Mike and crew) and band (thank you for being awesome) on the first floor. After midnight we moved up to the second floor which was COMPLETELY empty aside from the two of us. My friend and I danced for a good hour alone on the dance floor but realized towards the end of our dancing that the DJ was recording us dancing on his personal phone even though we had not given our permission for him to be recording us in any way. I approached the DJ (DJ Daddy J) and his MC but both were obstructive when I asked them to delete any photos/videos of myself and my friend. I eventually involved a manager (Tiffany) who was understanding and sympathetic. However, regardless of the on-staff manager's response my friend and I still left feeling incredibly violated. I hope that management from this point forward instills a sense of  importance for a customer's consent to be videoed or photographed while at this establishment. For the time being I will not be patronizing this place as I do not feel safe that my privacy will be respected by externally hired employees.

We ordered online for delivery by grub hub.  It took 95 minutes and the food was just average.  Also, the food was delivered to our hotel with no utensils or napkins.  We would not order from this restaurant again.  I updated my review to a 4 because most of the problem was the delay from Grub Hub.  The delivery delay likely impacted the taste of the food.  If you order from this restaurant pick it up yourself so it will be hot.  Also be sure to ask for utensils and napkins if you are staying in a hotel.

So while the name doesn't show that this is a Chinese restaurant, this doesn't take away from the fact that it has some pretty good takeout. It's hard to compare Chinese food places, and this one of the better ones I've had. It literally is set up as a takeout place, and that is understandable, as that's mostly what I've seen from Chinese restaurants (that aren't buffets, or PF Changs). It is also close to me, so I will be coming here for my Chinese takeout needs.
Just ordered from this place, food was fresh and flavorful. Looking forward to trying other items from the menu. This just became my to-go place for Chinese food.

Tijuana Flats is a great little Mexican restaurant that's close to my office. Everything I've ordered has always been delicious. My favorite part about this restaurant is the hot sauce bar. I love spicy food and having a hot sauce bar to try different spicy sauces is a dream come true for me. I feel like it only takes a few minutes for them to take your order and have your food delivered to your table. Which is great when you were in a rush.
Magalys did my hair and it was gorgeous !! Made a new wave of confidence arise ! Thank you so much for the make over

Went back to Thai Lotus for an impromptu dinner after work on a Friday night and it was packed which is great for this restaurant. I ordered the Tom Kha noodle soup medium heat and it was amazing. Lots of good, fresh flavors and it came steaming hot to the table. I also had the Thai iced coffee which was good as well.

What a treasure.  Delightful delicacies of very modest price.  Truly a treat with which to reward your inner Parisienne.  Patisserie standards of varying confection include Napoleon and eclair, but a variety of cakes do not disappoint.  Staff are extremely friendly and accommodating.

I've been to Southern Cross for both brunch and dinner.  Dinner was very good, love the fried pickles (little greasy, but to be expected with anything deep fried), fried oysters were well seasoned and creamy, fried chicken was very good, etc.  Also a good beer list.  Brunch, however, was very disappointing.  Maybe my expectations were too high after how much I enjoyed dinner, but the descriptions on the menu were much more appetizing than the meals themselves.  Gravy was way too meaty and not creamy enough, fried chicken sandwich wasn't cohesive (it was like all ingredients were just tossed on rough white bread with no effort to tie them together), omelette was very flat and dense, etc.  In summary, good spot for dinner, but do yourself a favor and skip the brunch.

Be aware of this bait and switch company. They get into your house by advertising 70% off. Once the salesman got in all he tried to do was get a commitment to spend $40,000 to $50,000 on our flooring. Once he realized we were not interested to spend that much, he wasn't even interested to talk about his 70% off pricing and left without showing us any samples.
I love this place. An British Pub meets Indian cuisine feel. Nice terrace, friendly staff, great appetizers.

The good get better... and this place just keeps getting better.  Loved it and can't wait to go again.   Nice staff.  Food options should have something for everyone... even those of us that love spice.  Beer selection and personal taps are fun.  They are new and we drive by enough to see that demand was very high from day one, i.e. you could see between our first visit and second that there was a learning curve, but no worries now!  I think of this as a perfect spot for small groups.  Prices are reasonable.  This is the best  setup I have seen for watching games in big screen HD, with a good view from every table.  

Enjoy!

one of our favorite places to go. crowd is fairly large no matter what night you go. most nights they have a theme.. "taco tuesday" etc. there is a pretty good variety of their craft beers. ask your server for samples of different ones... that way you end up with a great selection to choose from

The BBQ here was phenomenal. My only regret is that I shared a 3 meat plate with my boo - I should have told him to get his own. We got the ribs, pulled pork, and brisket, with mac & cheese and beans as sides.

Was only here one night. We also arrived in the middle of that night because we had been driving from California. The room was nicely kept and didn't have a chemical smell when I walked in. The bathroom was also nicely kept. The only problem I had was that the ceiling lights in the bathroom had a bunch of mold.. Other than that, my stay was pretty good. They also give out a 2 for 1 coupon card for the buffet upstairs.

The business owners are WONDERFUL people. The friendliest people ever. They help you out when you're not sure what to order since their are so many different meals to choose from. Very down to earth people. That made me love this place right off the bat.

The food here, however, had me sold. I've tried about 5 different things from here so far and every single one has been so delicious. It is sooooo good I don't know how she does it. Everything is full of flavor and cooked to perfection. You will not be disappointed. They deserve all the business in the world.
Horrible service, The hospitality here was completely biased and the lack of amenities for family's is poor.
Melba's has serves just about anything Cajun or creole you could want, plus daiquiris. The fish & shrimp po boy was my first in New Orleans, and it set the bar high. No complaints at all.

Spicy is not my thing, so I get the southern which means not spicy at all. But this place is great, yummy chicken while eating with locals and tourists alike. During lunch, eating in equals a long wait and/or line.

Food was fine but service was TERRIBLE. 4 people ( 2 couples) and dinner almost took 2 hours. Ordered an appetizer specifying that I would like it out first. Over 25 minutes later, app comes out with the food. Than we don't see our server again (No, would you like another drink etc) until he brings our bill. 20 minutes later, he comes back and we ask for a split bill and he responds he can only do it down the middle. We won't be back.

Express Scripts is a legal rip off.  Tell me how is it possible that they can give me a 90 day supply but my local pharmacy cant?  Here is a big 1-2-3 FU to Express Scripts and legal illicit scam
On top of the above, their customer service for MEDICINE (which we all know is about SAVING LIVES and not the all might dollar? ) sucks
after attempting to enroll in the auto refill program 3x i finally gave up and went back to my local pharmacy.

Medicine is in a sad state of affairs

There's no one else I can blame but myself for choosing to come to Grounded at the St. Louis airport. All of my intuitions were telling me not to go and literally go anywhere else in the terminal like Starbucks or the vending machine, but nooooo I HAD to try something different. 

I wasn't in too big a rush THANK GOD because the service here is slowwww, but like, comically slow. I was actually kind of entertained. I got the veggie burger, it took 15 minutes (?) it was underwhelming and sad and now you know and now I know.

I just want to say screw your hospital! You told my husband you were in our network he gave you our insurance card! And then we get a letter saying oh sorry you aren't in our network and you owe us 15,000$! Your not getting a penny from us! BECAUSE YOU LIED and did nothing for husband you couldn't even check on him for hours! We will see you Court! 





What horrible service. We have been waiting for 6 hours... my husband took the sticky things off his chest so the machine registered him as "dead" still no one has came in to check on him. He's been "dead" for minutes. What

This restaurant is a staple weekend quick breakfast or lunch location. I can't get enough! 

Lenny is a fantastic server who is thoughtful, efficient, and remembers your order each time you come in, which is a great personal touch. 

The food is delicious. I have to recommend the eggs with corned beef hash in the mornings, also I love the coffee! 

Great restaurant, I just moved to Davis Island and plan on making this a regular weekend activity.

Love the atmosphere. Very relaxed but at the same time very classy. A group of four of us sat by the fire place (not lit) under the Greek head wall art. Was very cozy and a great place to converse. We had the roasted cauliflower, the bruchetta, and a pizza( don't rememeber the name) (had mushrooms, roaster garlic and spinach) and everything came out prompt and tasty. The cauliflower is to die for. I highly recommend it. Great place for date night or girls night out!
Weird location but cheap and quick very quick! Good prices. I can't complain one bit!

Very nice place! My friend and I got standard pedicures which were very well done. Very friendly and happy staff. Excellent and huge choice of nail polish! Everything looked clean. Prices were average for this type salon. Our pedis were $27 and I got flowers painted for an additional $5. There was a 5% discount for checking in on Yelp. I would definitely recommend, and return to, RT Nails and Spa!
Really good sushi. Glad we stopped here for dinner and will definitely be back. Great, friendly service.
Local and trusted friends recommended the Pimms Cup but we arrived to find the Napoleon House closed from July 4 - July 20, 2010. Just FYI.

I've been going to Honey's since they only had the Northern Liberties location and am glad to see that as they expand they continue to be the best brunch spot in neighborhood.  Sure, it's cash only - but the prices are so reasonable it's not a ridiculous request.  This trip, we sat at the bar (loose term - it's BYOB), and enjoyed Sunday brunch.  Although we were traditional in the time we chose to go, you can have breakfast foods all day (until close in the evening). 

Step inside and you may see a crowd awaiting seating if it's on the weekend.  Unlike the NoLibs location though, finding a table during the weekdays may be an easier task.  

I still haven't been for dinner, but the menu makes me think I should.

Located in the Irish Channel, a few blocks past Magazine Street, Parasol's is a bar and causal restaurant.  Dive bars and po'boys just go together, right?  Parasol's bar is your classic no frills watering hole, good for a little conversation and beer.  The crowd was a healthy mix of regulars and tourists during my late afternoon weekend visit, with the bar filling up and half emptying out a few times while I was there.  And why was I there?  I was there for the po'boys.  I after completing a self-guided tour of the garden district I realized I needed a beer and a glass of water, and that Parasol's was a mere 10 minute walk away.  I had recently had lunch and was in no way hungry, but I accepted that gluttony was in the cards for me because Parasol's is known for their po'boys.  Torn between the regular shrimp po'boy and the firecracker shrimp po'boy I was persuaded by the person who took my order to go with the firecracker shrimp because "we are the only ones in New Orleans with it on the menu".  I was not disappointed with my choice, in fact it was my favorite po'boy of the trip.  The shrimp are breaded and fried and dipped in a type of spicy buffalo sauce.  It is a spicy sandwich to be sure, but not too intense.  The bread was perfect, and the accompaniments (lettuce, tomato, pickles, rémoulade sauce) were spot on in terms of ratio and quality.  I think the pickles in the sandwich were the ingredient that pushed it over the top for me.  One word of caution, when ordering you must choose between regular and large size.  I ordered regular and it was a foot long.  I have no idea how big a large is, but I'd proceed with caution.  Also, as with all the other po'boys I ate in Nola, the sandwiches are over flowing with shrimp, so even if you are real hungry, remember you have a whole sandwich to eat plus the 20 shrimp on the side that fell off the sandwich.

This place is a like pizza roulette. You never know if it's going to be good or bad. 

I've ordered from here multiple times (so many times that I even got enough points for a free pizza). I would say 2/3 times the pizza is under or over cooked. 1/3 times the delivery guy is late. 1/3 the delivery guy is a creep. 

If you're willing to risk a good meal, order from here. But there are also better family owned pizza shops that deliver as well. 

I really only ordered from here so much because free pizza excites me hahaha. 

The chicken bites are good though, and their dipping sauces are flavorful. Remember to ask for red peppers because they don't have it on hand unless you order it in advance.

This place is a HUGE find in this "neck of the woods."  They have a very sizable selection of organic vitamins, minerals, tonics, etc.  Have skincare, toiletries, and organic produce!  A gem!  The owner is very friendly and knowledgable...and the prices are very reasonable!  I am and will continue to be a regular for as long as I live in this area.

AWFUL AWFUL AWFUL!!!!!! Ordered shirts from this company and Custom Ink at the same time because Custom Ink did not have the color tank top I needed. Same graphic used for both companies. Finished product from Custom Ink was amazing. Finished product from Rush Order Tees was such poor quality...they added extra lines to the design that were NOT in the original graphic, the screen print is flaking off, design is difficult to make out. Looking at the two side-by-side shows an incredible difference and really illustrates just how awful their products are. To top it off, I was just told that no one can help me today even though they are "open 7 days a week" I have to wait until Monday. Very poor customer service. Terrible product. DO NOT WASTE YOUR MONEY!!!!! ORDER FROM CUSTOM INK!!!!!!

Just left here. Ordered the family pack. Added the ribs and the pork. First off they forgot to put the ribs and pork in the bag. So once the cook came out to look he came back with a tiny container of pork. I asked him if this was what was $5.95 and he just looked at me like I was speaking a foreign language. Then he brought out another tiny container which he claimed was a 1/2 slab of ribs. There were 3 tiny rib bones in the box. Needless to say this is not what I was used to being from south Florida where they were a common restaurant. Now let's get to the staff. When we got there one girl was working the register. Her name was Chasity and she looked as happy to be there as someone waiting at the DMV. She took our order. Handed us a buzzer and she was done. Maybe she was mad because there were about 50 people in line and she was the only person on the register. There were about 20 employees there total. 3 of them were just standing around doing nothing but complaining and taking about how they can't wait to get off to "turn up". We briefly saw someone who looked like he may be a manager or an owner but he just was telling some other employees not to just be sitting at a table talking. This was a totally unacceptable experience and will be my last at a pollo tropical in Tennessee. Don't waste your time or money here until the management fixes their obvious lack of control over the staff or quality of the food and service.
I absolutely love this place! I have nothing bad to say except I wish they would stay open past midnight.
We had pizza here tonight and it was really good. Cozy little joint with cheap beer and great pizza. Loved it!

Terry is amazing!  He did amazing work on my foot tattoo, which is also my first tattoo.  He was so nice and explanatory and the tattoo is beautiful.  It healed perfectly and didn't have any bleeding or heavy scabbing.  All the people in the shop were awesome and easy to work with.  Very clean and nice inside and incredibly reasonable.  I live in LA or I would be sending all my friends get their work done there.  A+++++

This is my favorite Coffeebar in Reno. I came from San Francisco, CA and after I tried their coffee I would say really the best even compare with lots of  coffee shops that I tried in Bay Area. I would definitely recommend to all of my friend once they in town please do tried their coffee before get back to your own town. Start with cashiers, they're cashiers are really nice and warmly welcome you, after that you will also meet their best baristas and they all carrying the most beautiful smile, it means a lot to all of us and it made our day. Long conversation short come try yourself and find out. Have a good wonderful drinks yelpers.

Probably one of my favorite beer experiences.  

Pro's:
1) The pale ale I ordered was fantastic.  It's rare that I'll drink a beer and be impressed by how flavorful and aromatic it is, but that was certainly the case.  
2) The people, both patrons and servers.  There were families there with babies, dogs, etc.  And, no college/club type crowds.  Very pleasant atmosphere.
3) The food truck was a welcome treat, and contributed to the outdoor feel of the place.
Con's
1) The neighborhood is a bit intimidating if you're not familiar with the area.  We parked a couple of blocks away.

Fabulous new studio. The owner, Tasha, is amazing and does first rate one on one Pilates classes. She really customizes it to your needs and abilities and is excellent at reading the challenges in your body just by looking at you. Amazing! They also have barre classes and yoga and Pilates classes. It's great. Check it out! Great new addition to the neighborhood.

We had the chef's tasting menu. Each dish was good, well balanced, if not a little seasoned for my tasted and a little "one note" considering my expectations. It was extremely, extremely loud. So loud that we could barely hear each other or our servers; that was very disappointing. The decor is interesting, almost more so than the food,which, while good, wasn't really special. I didn't walk out of the restaurant feeling like I had an experience worthy of $100 per person (plus one bottle of very good sake for $94). In truth, all 4 of us were underwhelmed.

This place is wonderful! I saw it one day as I was walking down the Delmar Loop and had to try the food! Another great take out joint during COVID-19, but they also offer distance and outdoor seating. 

We ordered the Chicken Shawarma, Beef Shawarma and Falafel sandwiches! They were all excellent! Each had a special taste to them. I think my favorite were Beef and Chicken Shawarma! The meat was tender, well cooked, and seasoned extremely well. The flavors for each were deliciously unique with veggies that added a nice crunch. 

The Hummus and Baba Ganoush were also both amazing! The Hummus was balanced well with the flavors of chickpea, tahini and saltiness, while the Baba Ganoush had a smokiness with creamy texture.  

Looking forward to having this place nearby! We will be back!

Absolutely will be referring everyone I know.  First off John is genuine and honest.  I cannot express how important that is with auto repair places.  So often we feel like we are getting taken for a ride, however not at John Carney's Auto Repair.  He treats you like family and there was absolutely no upcharges or hidden fees.  He finished the work in a timely manner and called me with a price prior to starting work.  No surprises.  I already referred my brother and friend.  Do yourself a favor and check him out.  You will not be disappointed.

I went into MOD pizza to order salad for myself, my sister, and my 90 year old mother.  One of the "associates" was putting out the pizza and salad toppings without a mask on!  As a physician who is "on the front lines" during this pandemic, I was disgusted.  Needless to say, I left and went to Panera (Bread CO) to get salads for our lunches.  What is wrong with people who would handle food, serve it to strangers, and not provide protection?
This place is a pleasant surprises.  Ended up here on a whim and couldn't be happier!  The food taste so fresh!  The building is so unique and the furniture is super rad!

Great pizza, one of the best so far I have had in the area. They were quick to have our order ready for takeout and even though I wasn't of fan of any of their specialty pizza's we custom made one which was really good. Less greasy than say Flying Pie and the crust was a little harder which I like. We had the pepperoni and pineapple, our favorite. Pineapple was just the dole canned kind, but wasn't bad. Their cheesy twists are a must! A little doughy, but still delicious!
Great beer, food and staff. A must place to go if you are anywhere close to Kennett Square.

The food was amazing,  the service friendly,  and great menu selection.  It is BYOB.  The dining room is small though so if you are looking for social distancing,  go during slow times.   We went for a mid-afternoon snack and it was perfect.   Their pizza was excellent as we ordered take out another time.

Quite simply the best baked goods I have had in Philly...  The second best cheese danish ever anywhere (best was Marvelous Market in DC).

Great butcher with fresh meats, poultry etc.  Eclectic mix of grocery items.

This is not authentic Vietnamese food. If you like simple flavors, then this is the place for you. Summer rolls have lettuce, shrimp and noodle and no herbs. The fish sauce is bland. The dipping sauce for summer rolls is watered down.   The banh mi barely has any veggies in it and they don't put any pickled daikon, just carrots. I ordered take out and waited about 20 minutes or more for my food while two customers that came after me got their food first. I was clearly upset with the wait and the woman who served me could see it and just spoke in her language to the man that worked with her in front of me.  I will not be returning and don't recommend this place to anyone. If you don't know Vietnamese food then you don't know what you are missing. I would not recommend this place at all.

I was in the area visiting and my friend and I came in on Sunday.
I got a full set, and today four of them have chipped and the top coat is peeling. :(
I really wanted to like this place we were considering coming back regularly regardless of the drive just because the salon is cute, clean, and the people were super sweet, outgoing, & fun.
But I've honestly have never had a full set chip on me this badly or at all any other time. 
I'm pretty disappointed.

I can't even give one star for this place. We called ahead and made a reservation near the bar at 10:30 pm.  I told them we had a big group and just wanted drinks when we called.. They said no problem.. We we got there they were so rude and would not even seat is even though they had a table waiting for is because we were not going to be ordering food.  Terrible experience and will never go back.

A friendly Jack answered my Togo order call.  The food was tasty for eating it on the go!  Next time I'll have to try more!  Street taco trio and SW chop we're both above par.  It was the dead hours between lunch and dinner on a Saturday but there were a couple of tables there.  I'd suggest to stagger your employees' in-times so they don't get burnt out from the downtime.  There were a lot milling around.  If we're in the area I'll bring the family in for a bite!  Thanks Jack!

Nom...Nom...Nom  Are you looking for a good old fashioned sloppy, juicy, delicious beef burger with all the fixings?  Well then this place is a must!  Not only are the burgers delicious....the fresh fries will cause you to eat until you hurt yourself.  Burger heaven
I've flown all over the country and abroad. Still one of the best airports! Security is always super fast. All the staff are friendly and very helpful. All about that Hoosier Hospitality!!

A small and intimate bar / restaurant in north Philadelphia. You can tell this is a bar frequented by locals the second you walk in. There's a nice outdoor seating area right on the sidewalk (perfect for people watching) and if it wasn't so chilly we probably would have sat outside to enjoy ourselves. Me and a friend decided to sit at the bar even though it wasn't super packed on a Saturday afternoon. The bartender Eddie gave us immediate service and was super friendly. He even let me try a few brews so that I could pick the one they fit my taste. I ordered the brunch burger based on Eddies recommendation and he was spot on. It was filling but not greasy and tasted like it was fresh off the grill. This place is a gem and you should certainly check it out if your in the neighborhood. Daily Cocktail Daily Cocktail

Picked this business at random for a last minute (about 1:30 pm) Valentines Day order . They got a great bouquet of roses delivered by end of day at a very reasonable price. Best on line experience I have ever had with flowers. Highly recommend.

Literally the worse dd I've ever been to! First time I went. Asked for a hazelnut ice coffee and received a caramel ice coffee. Second time my coffee was so dark after asking light with cream. And thirds I orders a bagel. It was hard as a rock and so rubbery I couldn't even break it or bite it! Never going back!

I took my eight year old to Busch Garden this year (2016). She was hurt two times on the rides. The first one was on the very old ride called Scorpion. Her neck was injured and 8 months later she still has on an off pain. The second time she was injured was on the Blimpy Water Ride. This ride has no safety belt and I was sitting behind her. When it came down the water drop, I was pushed on her and she hurt her adult front tooth by hitting it on the seat in front of her.  Her tooth was moved to the front. I decided to report the incident this time. I should have reported the first incident on the Scorpion as well.  I told the risk management that these rides should be shut down due to not being safe, specially for the small kids. They only said if her permanent tooth needs work they will pay for it. That is all. I never heard back with a follow up even though the incident was reported to their risk control department. She has pain eating hard food now and the Dentist told us she might lose her otherwise healthy front tooth one they down the road.  I no longer trust Busch Garden and refuse to take my daughter on the old rides. I came to the conclusion that this company is greedy and only cares about making profits.

Woman working is RUDE! Will never come here again. No the laundromat doesn't need to be open but I'm sure she needs a paycheck more than staying home and making no money. Needs to learn some customer service.

They offer 3 different levels of memberships one is standard for like $50 something , VIP $70 something  and all inclusive for like $120 something all with $100 dollars initiation fee that can be waived.  The differences in price mean you get to use there towels and what areas of the gym and equipment you get access to.

Being from NYC and having lived in South Beach FL, Washington DC, Salt Lake City and Houston TX, I am comparing to other gyms in the same price range for service, group classes, and cleanliness. 

Location is not the best.   Yes, it's in the heart of Nashville, but it is located in a hard to get to area and parking is not really easy.   Actually it is really weird because of all the construction going on, so maybe just maybe this problem will change after construction is over.  An upside is you do get 2hr complimentary parking if can find one in their lot.

Friendly stuff but kind of pretentious.   The place looks ok and small especially for a name like "WORLD GYM." The front desk and membership areas are small and open.   They have a mini store with t-shirts with the name of the gym.  Quality ok, but not the best. 

Main floor is home to the cardio machines and a big open studio.   Kind of a let down when I found out there is only one dance class on Friday afternoon.  There were a few other classes offered.

Downstairs I will call it the basement -is dark, busy and smelly. As soon as you go down the stairs there was very powerful smell of sweat.   The bathroom smelled of urine.  So needless to say at that point I was already like thank you but NO thank you. 

I did ask the owner about more classes.   I think his name is Johnny. He said people don't participate in classes they offer, and will not pay for a full service club.

They do offer a few extras like towel service, massage chairs and red light therapy.  However, you also get that at Planet fitness for only $10 or $20 a month and at least clean bathrooms.

This compared to places NY or DC Sport Club, Equinox in NYC and Miami, The Villa Sports Club at the Woodlands in Texas,  The GYM at City Creek in Salt Lake City. All these places offer a full service club for less then what this place is asking for.

In my opinion "WORLD GYM" is at the same level as a 24 hrs Fitness or Planet Fitness,  but with prices that rival a full service sports club.  Not worth it.

The worst!  An appointment means noticing. I understand a wait, but 45 minutes and they didn't even bring the car in and my entire appointment was supposed to take 40 minutes. I mentioned more than once I had to be out at a certain time. No apologies from them, just excuses. And when I made the spot they had the part (battery) in stock, when I get there they don't even carry the brand anymore, so how did they have it 2 days previously? It was a warranty battery and then they say, they need to do an entire diagnostic to check the alternator, probably to sell me something I don't need. I only went there because it was under warranty. I'll go to another pep boys, this one was always the worst! Liars and scammers. They almost ruined my engine before. Thought maybe in 2 years they changed, guess not.

In a city of cheese steaks and new age foods, Philly is caught between healthy vegan type dishes and all out cardiac arrest type meals. South St Diner fills the void, it's a good old time spot that offers greasy spoon options such as the typically burger and fries but they also offer healthier options such as salads as well. 

My favorite meal here is the buffalo chicken wrap. For under ten bucks you'll get a wrap and a generous portion of fries. They drizzle in ranch, lettuce, and tomatoes for good measure. 

The service here is somewhat spotty. I've had good experiences in general however. I think they could do a slightly better job of minding whether my beverage could use a refill.

I came here for a haircut with Katie... now, I hadn't gotten my hair cut in over a year (and it showed). I sat down with Katie, asked her to make me look good but to keep it low-maintenance, and goodness gracious did she deliver. By the time I left, not only did my hair look great, I was relaxed and had thoroughly enjoyed my entire time. Katie knows how to keep the conversation going and truly made me feel at home. 

I cannot attest to the rest of the facilities, but the entire place was clean, relaxing, and friendly. 

In short (teehee), I'll make sure to get my hair cut more than once a year just so I can go back to this lovely little paradise.

Some prices are fine other items are expensive. But they always have only a few checkouts open no matter what time I go. And most of the time the line takes forever. They took out the self checkouts when it converted from a pathmark. Why?  There is no quick pop in there. The employees do not try to rush and the only reason I go is I live walking distance. But there prices are increasing since their opening so soon I won't bother.

I had a Groupon and when I called to schedule the appt they did a bait-and-switch and told me I could not use it for the services advertised and paid for. She said, "Oh, Groupon made a mistake." This is fraudulent and unethical. The merchant approved the Groupon contract. I would not go here.

Excellent place! I am a breakfast snob and this place was nothing short of amazing! I ordered the eggs Benedict on top of their sweet potatoes and it was so delicious. The homemade hollandaise was a hit! The decor in this restaurant was so fabulous! Our server was also excellent. I can't wait to go back!
Good menu options. Safe choices. Never failed me in terms of service. Will go here again. Love the steak here as well. Keep it up UNO!

I called to pick up a pizza and was told it would be about an hour until it was ready, so I said never mind, and I called elsewhere. It was a busy Friday night and everyplace was going to take a long time so I called back and ordered it and confirmed the pick up time.  Parking is a hassle in the location on Central so it took about 10 minutes to get a spot a block away, and when I went to pick it up it wasn't ready. In fact they didn't start making it until after I had paid, now well over an hour from my telephone order.

They guy making the pizza didn't seem to be in much of a hurry, and he wasn't making any other pizzas - the place only has a few tables and wasn't very busy - so I was feeling a little displeased at the wait, but the pizza actually cooked up quite quickly, so I guess the intentionally wait to give it out fresh. Ingredients were not generous but they were actually fairly balanced and seemed fresh. When I was handed the box I was surprised at how light the pizza was and actually walked out not thrilled with the experience so far, between the wait and nonchalance and parking and then the very light pizza. In fact before I got home I had decided I didn't really like the place. But then I ate the pizza and was happy. It  was actually really good, bot the think heavy doughy cheesy thing I've have grown to expect, but something different, fresh and very tasty. Do yes I will be back, though I will probably avoid busy nights.
We stopped in here on the way to Atlantic City. We had Great service from a very friendly staff, great breakfast food, and very large portions! We would definitely come back here!

We came here after taking our son to the Children's Museum across the street.  The food was great!  I ordered the Tarpon Springs with Kalimata olives, feta cheese, and peppers, my husband ordered a pizza with artichokes and mushrooms, and my son got a pepperoni.  We each ordered a personal size, and my only complaint was they were a little small for $7-9 each, but still plenty of food.  We'll come back to this place for sure!

The Spectra Wellness team provides exemplary care for their patients. Their focus on prevention and wellness is a model that should be used in all healthcare. I was recently challenged by a serious medical condition and Dr Koche and her staff provided exemplary care and referrals. Additionally, she gave me encouragement and confidence in handling my challenge. This is medicine practiced as it should be.

I used to love Bar Louie! This was my favorite place for me and my friends for years. This was a go-to.

I took my family there after the Walk For Autism for my 4-year-old. There were 8 of us and we were ready to eat. First, it took 40 minutes to get our drinks. The waitress then brought out plastic forks and knives for us to eat with. After we found out the waitress who was working pretty much alone, she informed us our food would be out soon. This was almost an hour after we ordered. 

Second, we didn't get everything with the drinks. We ordered bloody marys and it came with the works...bleu cheese curds, olives, bacon...we didn't get any of that. We had to ask for that. Also, my wife can't have sugar or preservatives, so she ordered hers with kettle one. They brought out three bloody's and couldn't tell us what kind of vodka was in which. 
Then our food comes. Here we go. If all else fails the food is going to be tops! It wasn't! Everything was cold. I mean everything. We could send it because this was over an hour after our arrival. We were ready to eat and go. We alert the waitress after we couldn't find her for another fifteen minutes. She apologizes. It was a lot of her fault. She was awesome! If it wasn't for her we would have left hours ago. 

The manger comes. I tell him of our experience and he doesn't even listen. He dismisses everything I said as if I was asking for a handout. We blow money on a regular. This was a family outing for dinner after a fundraiser at our favorite place in the CWE. He automatically assumes we want something for free and walks off with an attitude. And all we were doing is giving feedback on a place we love to frequent. Boyd was the manager. And if he is still there I will never go back. 

He was unprofessional, to say the least. 

Bar Louie!      Please! Fix!  this!

I wasn't really impressed. 

The food came out extremely quickly. Our server was very knowledgeable about the menu and took good care of us. 

The food was good, but it's... small for the price. I started off with the gnocchi, which isn't really gnocchi. It's served in a block style. It was delicious though and the mushrooms they used were perfect. I had the squid ink gigli as my entree, and I was not a fan. It didn't come together as a cohesive dish. I did try the pumpkin ravioli, and that was FANTASTIC. 

We got coffee to end the meal, and they only offer one type. I think it might have been a cappuccino? It was good, though. 

We ordered a side of the squash which was EXTREMELY overcooked. The management handled it well, they took it away, took it off our bill, and comped our coffees.

I had high hopes for this place, which is maybe why I was disappointed. It was loud, there was a TERRIBLE odor in the patio space (luckily we weren't seated there, but I smelled it walking through), and just not that great. I probably won't return.

We love this place!!!!  The steak noodle soup is the best, and we always order BBQ Pork spring rolls, which are amazing!  This place is so awesome, the wait is never that long, and they bring your food to you pretty quick!

I'm a barista who is used to extremely strong, chicory cafe au laits.. I ordered an iced cafe au lait with vanilla almond milk and instead was given half of a regular iced coffee and half milk, and unfortunately it tasted mostly like water. I was nervous to return it as I never really do that kind of thing but did spend more than I expected on it, and was met with extreme rudeness and aggression from the woman who made my coffee when I asked for a little bit more coffee in my cup. She sharply explained to me that it was my fault because I ordered a drink that is primarily made with milk -which I am aware of. I explained politely that I just expected a bolder flavor like in other cafe au laits I have had (and made) in the past. Oftentimes, they are made with Very strong brewed or concentrated coffee. She aggressively dumped more coffee into my cup and passed it over telling me that I should have ordered something else. I felt embarrassed and anxious, and will not be returning. Even if I was wrong and she had been having a rough day (which happens so often as a barista- customers can grate on your nerves!), I don't think it was fair to treat someone this way.

My second and last experience here was awful! I went on a Sunday afternoon. Although they seemed busy I didn't have to wait to get my nails done. I got my usual acrylic fill over top of my real nails and a gel nail polish top. I got a black tip manicure, instead of the usual white tip. First things first. The nail tech didn't bother cutting my cuticles and pushing them back the first or second time I was there. After about a week they look like crap and need to be filled again. I suppose that is to get people to return more often then usual because I have never heard of any nail salon techs not taking care of your cuticle when getting a manicure. Now this time I get the black tip and as Sue is applying the clear coat she smears streaks of black in every single nail. I pointed it out and she says sorry and continues like normal. OK. I let it go because I needed to be somewhere and it wasn't a complete disaster. Yet. Later that day I notice some of my nails are not completely flat and smooth. It felt like there was a bubble under the nail polish. Nothing I can do now. Three days later on Wednesday my gel nail polish starts chipping. If any one knows anything about gel nail polish is that its more expensive because its not suppose to chip for at least two/three weeks. My experience is that it never chips. Literally chunks of nail polish are chipping off every time I run my fingers through my hair or do dishes or flip through a stack of paper. I go back to Queen Nail Spa to get a refund for my $33 nails that didn't last more then three days. The manager guy first wanted to know who did my nails. Like it matters. They are messed up and the nail polish is half off. We figure out Sue was the one who did my nails. She was pretty pissed off that I was complaining about her work. I was trying to speak with the man about getting a refund and she continues to yell in my ear about her doing a good job and that she will fix them. No Sue you will not touch me ever. I had to interrupt my conversation with the man to ask her to stop yelling in my face. And as she walked away continued to yell at me, WITH A NAIL SALON FULL OF PEOPLE. Professionalism was radiating from this place.  The man refuses to give me a refund. He tells me they are not allowed to give them because he already spent the product to do my nails so they would lose money if they gave me my money back. He also told me that it didn't matter that I was unhappy and that I don't have to come back. What a JOKE! He finally offered to give me a gift certificate for the $18 I paid for the gel nail polish. Not even the total amount I spend including the crappy acrylic refill. If anyone feels the need to continue to go to this place after reading this review, stay far away from Sue and her manager husband. And go maybe as soon as they open so that the nail tech will actually pay attention to the job she/he should be doing and not whatever is going on in the front of the store.

I really enjoy Grimaldi's pizza. I've been fortunate to go to a few of them, and the pies here are as good as any. I didn't really care for the dining room at this location, and service was a bit slower than others I had been to, but it was still good pizza and a good time.

I've been hitting the fQ location by the Monteleone.

Today I was shopping on magazine store for some Ill swag and I stopped in....I like a light roast but settled on large drip coffee which came out to $ 3.01....the cashier gave me .99 cents change and I Instantly thought I had ingested mushrooms....I was tripping hardcore as I could not understand the .99 change and I still struggle with it and the fact that Michael Dukakis lost......

I tipped the .99 into the jar loudly and the walls breathed and flexed as the floor was also moving near the cream...into my cup!
Runner stretching by glass doors....fire station across slow moving street....foot traffic....

Even if the til was out of dollars: give me 4 quarters or a Sacajawea!!!! 

I would give you 4.75 stars if yelped allowed this and if my tab was rounded to the nearest dollar. 

I would like to discuss a company policy change that makes all prices even amounts and or you eat the overages. 

I mean a $3 cup of coffee....you must be covering your margins tenfold.....

I want my penny back.....

A normal dinner:  the food is decent, the drinks are pricey, and the service isn't the greatest.

Happy hour:  the appetizers and sushi are great, the prices are cheap, there are two time options 5-7 pm and 9-11 pm weekdays/ 10pm-midnight fridays and saturdays.  

So avoid the dining room and head to the bar!!

Had a gyro last week as a carry-out order.  While there was a ton of meat inside the pita (too much actually); the meat was dry and overcooked. It was really subpar.

With "Gyro" in the name; one would think they would get it right.  Sadly; they failed.

This is a great location but their quality of products is average to me. I recently went in (after multiple visits) to try a chai tea latte and it was "blah". However, I do love the sandwich options. My favorite so far is the bagel and lox because I always get this specific bagel (can't remember if it was garlic and onion) but it is very tasty with it.
Horrible service, waitress was incompetent and messed up our order. Manager came over to apologize and was extremely unhelpful and rude. Food also took long time and the Deviled eggs were very bland.

I can't say enough how blessed I feel to have had a fantastic experience with Roy today!  I brought my car in to have my bumper, which was in pretty sad shape, secured back to the car.  Roy inspected the bumper and quoted me 2hrs worth of work.  I told him that I wasn't looking for it to be aesthetically pleasing, just attached so that it would be safe to drive.  Not only did he reattach the bumper, he buffed out the marks, and didn't charge me!  Roy took amazing care of me and was very professional.  There is no doubt where I will be taking any of my vehicles for body work.  I also need to give Kudos to the gal at the front desk, and I'm sorry I didn't catch her name.  When I called last week to inquire, she answered all of my questions.  This morning I was greeted with a warm smile and the sweetest disposition.  Eric's CARSTAR has a great team!!!

Ridiculous conditions. The lights in the hsllway don't work snd the desk clerk is just its been like that. Then there is no hot water and the statement is the plumber is on the way. I am wondering what state they are coming from. They don't seem to care about the safety or well being of their guests.

I've typically liked Mimi's, but I recently had a not-so-great experience at the Reno location.  The muffins and french onion soup have always been my favorite (not together!).  I tried something new this time and had a fruit crepe; it was pretty good.  The issue was with the service.  The server took our drink orders, then took ages getting back to us.  He then left, saying he'd be back to take our breakfast orders shorty.  Once again, he took forever.  He didn't know any of the details about the items on the menu, and he had to come back out twice to ask us about things he should have originally.  While we were waiting for our food, a table of girls was seated next to us.  Before we got our food they all left because no one had come to even take drink orders yet; there was a great span of time here.  Like I said, the food was decent; just not worth the wait.

The doors to  the platform may not shut all the way and there may be dirt everywhere, but the bathrooms are clean, the escalators work, the trash is taken out, the benches are clean, the announcements are clean and accurate, the signs aren't broken, the walls are colorful, the ticket window is convenient, and there is a designated musician area.  Overall I'd say Septa is doing alright at this station.

You absolutely MUST go to a Third Friday open house event at the TDGF.  There's something for everyone from the very young to the young at heart.

The event is free but you could partake in the a few of the activities or shopping for $.  Feeling hungry?  They had light food and drinks for purchase: bottled beers, cocktails and canned sodas.  I had their pomegranate martini which was pretty good and got a raffle ticket with ever drink purchase.  The raffle ticket entered me into the hourly drawing for a free piece of glass.  Tonights pieces were a wine stopper, glass flower, large glass plate and a glass vase.  

In the main room they showed a number of glass demonstrations, it was interactive with the audience asking questions.  You could parooz through the gallery of art and glass plates, bowls, vases, ornaments, etc, all available for purchase or just sit an enjoy the one man guitar band in the main entryway.  

My step-mom and sister were feeling creative and got hand's-on with glass making by designing a tile and a pendant & earing set.  You arrange the hard glass pieces the way you want your design and they cure it for you, for pick up later in the week.  

The best entertainment by far was sitting on their outdoor patio and watching the belly and fire dancing.  They're interactive too, they pulled more than a few audience members into the circle to learn a few booty shaking moves.  It was a lot of fun and my favorite part of the night.

My family had more than a blast here this Friday, we'll probably still be talking about the event in years to come.  The hubby was will probably tell me how they made the plates and glassware when we look for a new dining set.  My younger brother will probably still be talking about their cool bathrooms, something about the faucet and seeing the water come out.  My sister will probably blush when she retells the story of her "5-minutes of fame" in the belly dancing circle.  My Dad will never get over the "pyros" and their amazing fire tricks.  And my step-mom will be glowing every time she wears her own designed pendant and earrings set, reminiscing about what a cool night we had at the Glass Factory.

This bar is TRASH. My boyfriend and I LOVE bar rescue so we decided we had to stop by. The drinks were expensive for bourbon street and disgusting. Very sugary and you would swear they were made in the machine and not by the bartender. Also, it took about 8 minutes to get service in a DEAD bar (on Saturday night) and one of the owners was arguing with a bartender in front of us. The show where they followed up said it was one of the most populated bars on bourbon. That was an absolute lie. Also, I doubt the quality of Jon Taffer's expertise. Sad experience.

I was just told that snapping a fan reminds the bar tender of the Orlando shooting. Aka he brings up a traumatic experience for our community to justify his basic opinion. If only we could all be so salty!! #TRASH

What's next? "I don't like your shirt, it reminds me of _____"

"I don't like your race it reminds me of ____"

"Welcome to FLORIDA! C'mon progress!" -Nobody

Ps. You can smoke cigarettes and literally choose to kill yourself but you cannot have a fan! #safetyfirst
Yummy food!

can't complain about any of the food we ordered....it was all tasty....certain dishes I wish they could give just a little more portion though

Bourbon mixed drink- Tried some of my wifes....Excellent

Edamame Dumplings- Melt in your mouth delicious...a little too much truffle taste though that hid the edamame taste

General Tso Soup Dumpling- Loved the strong ginger taste and went perfect with sriracha on the table

Chicken Bao Bun- My favorite dish of the night....even took an order to go..one of the best bao I ever had

Tuna Rice Cracker- Up there with the Bao...In the mood for one now

Hamachi Ceviche- Excellent

Crispy Rock Shrimp- I have had better elsewhere...good but not great

Crispy Brussel Sprouts- A little too salty but addicting...Great taste if less salty....Would recommend as a side dish rather than by itself

Kimchee Fried Rice- It was good but not excellent...Too buttery for me and lacked the heat and spices I like

Cone Ice Cream dessert- Too small but very good.  Would devour a larger size
Awesome sea bass tonight. Served with risotto and a Caesar Salad. Sea Bass was perfectly prepared. Moist and a gentle crispy finish. Hey... Half price bottles of wine in Wednesday night. What a deal!

I really love honeygrow, I do, and this one is so close to my job. The fact that it was created by my fellow Temple Alumni makes it so much better. The quality of food is so great, always fresh, and taste delicious. I've never had an experience where the food wasn't good. This location I usually go to during lunch, I order through the app in order to avoid standing in line during the lunch rush. They are pretty good about having the orders out in time BUT the reason I deducted 2 stars is because the last TWO times I've been here I've had an issue with my order and I don't usually notice until I get to my office and it's too late. 

I always ask for my sauce on the side because I usually have left overs for the next lunch day the first time I had a Create Your Own (CYO) stir fry with sauce on the side and they forgot it completely so I just ate it dry at work and brought in some soy sauce packets from home and mixed it with honey for sauce for my leftovers the next day. 


This time around I got a CYO salad with sauce on the side because I don't like for it to be soggy the next day. Well they put the sauce on the side but when I opened my salad there was also sauce on it! There's no way I'll be able to eat this tomorrow unfortunately so I'll just attempt to eat it for lunch and dinner. On the plus side it is a very yummy salad. Don't get me wrong this honeygrow provides good food and service but needs to pay more attention when preparing the orders.

My daughter and I stopped by the above mentioned food court location this evening for a quick bite. This location is fairly new to the food court and our first visit. I just have to say how courteous, polite and professional K. Konstantinos was. What a breath of fresh air he was!!! Someone who actually likes his job and takes pride in it. He couldn't do enough for us in this food court setting. He truly represents the Stewart's brand in an outstanding way. The food was well prepared and tasted great. I was very impressed by my visit tonight and will definitely be back. I'd be remised if not taking the time to make mention of the outstanding service and experience I had this evening. If your visiting they offer free refills on their drinks and are not bashful in letting you know so. A rarity amongst the other food court outlets. Try the Stewart's Black Cherry fountain.
Ordered the bahn mi nachos, great flavor and spicy but not overwhelmingly so. Lots of parking and the line moved pretty quickly.

So happy a brewery opened up within 10 minutes of where I live. Came here on a Thursday night and was surprised to see such a crowd. Crowded but still hometown feel. Friendly staff. Enjoyed the coffee porter. Will be back a lot!
Beautiful view, clean rooms, nice staff, cheap rates. Near Tampa Bay, Good if planning to take a cruise. Would definitely stay again.  Thank You!

I live very close to this establishment or I would drive farther, it's true 7/8 times out of 10 order is wrong. My worst experience was a egg bagel that was molded...not just a little ( which is still unexceptable) but obviously green with mold, and they served it. It's almost easier just to call your order in to Nashville Biscuit House and pick it up or for a bagel go to Bagel Face Bakery is on Main Street, their bagels are better than average with a good selection.

In and out in 5 minutes because of the extremely rude bar tender.

Have to provide one star because of the female bartender working the first level bar around 645pm. So much attitude and you could tell she enjoyed being rude. You are in customer service so you should try and provide great service instead of feeling a power trip giving customers bad experiences by saying no.

The security at the entrance was kind and greeted us and apologized for the negative experience we received in the 5 minutes we were there as we were leaving. 

The music sounded really nice too so wish she didn't ruin so bad for us that we no longer want to return.

It is a competitive street of bars. If you want great service go to Ole Red or really any of the bars around and avoid this one.

The food here was surprisingly and disappointingly unappealing. The food was not well seasoned AT ALL. Do not try their gumbo, jambalaya or their red beans and rice--your taste buds don't deserve that. Not a real NOLA place. This place is a tourist trap.

A Tampa Bay "top 50" for cheap eats and let me tell you, this place is a MUST for tacos!!!

Attached to a little Mexican grocery store in Pinellas Park there is a small restaurant, almost like a deli type set up with seating inside and outside. The tacos (which they were listed in the top 50 for) were only 1.89 each! Full of flavor and 6 or 7 different meats to choose from made me very happy, my favorite was probably the carnitas but the carne asada and chicken were also very good. 

Also delicious beans and rice, authentic bottled Mexican drinks and homemade horchata. 

Inexpensive. Delicious. Authentic.

I recently had a remarkably good experience at this store!  I came in with a lot of pent up frustration with past management and a bad product. Rudy, the store manager (and part of the NEW management) could not have been more gracious and understanding. This was an opportunity for him to say "sorry, there's nothing I can do about the purchase you made so long ago", and then try to sell me something new. Instead, he advised me of the manufacturer's program to deal with the complaint and I was able to order a replacement through them at a significant savings. 

I cannot say enough positive things about Rudy. I heartily recommend this business because of its excellent management and customer relations. Their products, now that they have addressed the issue I had, are fabulous too!

Fit2Run has a great selection of running shoes, clothing, and gear. The two stars they get is due to the customer service.  I walked in knowing I need to get a thorough foot evaluation.  So after taking a few moments to look over the shoes, I sought out an employee for assistance. As one of the other commenters pointed out, the employees are primarily college students who look like they would rather be anywhere else.  When I told the sales person what I needed she looked and acted rather annoyed, but she did help me out and did seem rather knowledgable.  While I was waiting for her to bring me some shoes to try on I noticed the staff standing around talking and customers only being helped when they asked for it.  I do not usaully key in on what other customers experiences are, but this stood out.

Understaffed or disorganized? After being seated by hostess had to ask how to get a waitress to order food and beer. Ordered beer flight which came with no identification or explanation of which beer is which. Music was great.

This place has its ups and downs. Usually its a good place to gather a group of friends and get some food and drinks. Usually.

However, from time to time groups of belligerent people enter in vast numbers and ruin it for everyone else. 

Another thing is that they often put the volume of sporting events so high that it literally hurts. There is nothing better than watching sports and hearing the announcers voice screaming in both ears at a piercing volume.

About the food. The food is top notch and I would go there just for the food.

I'm so happy Pizza Ranch has come to Tennessee! I had heard amazing reviews from coworkers originally from the Midwest and was on countdown for them to open. They definitely live up to the hype. The fried chicken is some of the best I've ever had, and the Buffalo chicken mac n cheese pizza is my new favorite. I haven't had anything bad there! The employees are super friendly and yes, a lot of them are high school kids (probably their first job), but they are kind, courteous, and you can see them wiping down tables as fast as they can to get customers seated ASAP. This will be a family spot once a week for us!

Kayne's is an excellent steakhouse.  Though I went solo to check it out, it's an excellent place to entertain a group or have a romantic dinner because of the variety of rooms/settings it offers in upscale style and the modest noise level which allows one to conduct a conversation in relatively normal tones.  The service was excellent, I enjoyed the huge iceberg wedge topped with roquefort (?) cheese/dressing and tomatoes, bacon, and boiled egg to the side, and the progression of prime beef gave me a nice sampling of "Wagyu" beef which I had never heard of before (delicious).

Knowing my appetite I didn't get sides or desserts, so I can't speak to that.  I was disappointed in their relative lack of single malt scotch selections  (they do have the usual suspects of Glenlivet, Glenfiddich, and a couple of Macallan's), but I did enjoy their Garden Tonic made with Hendrick's gin and "muddled cucumber."  I thought it was a bit over-priced, but I'm not familiar with the Nashville market.

All in all, if looking for a special steak dinner, I recommend . . .

Let me start with the positive. The space is really cool and the outdoor patio is comfortable and inviting.
That being said, the food was some of the absolute worst I have ever had. The menu leaves a lot to be desired. The food is bland and and arrived ice cold, like it had been frozen and microwaved for its big moment, and the service was slow and painful. No water, no complimentary saltless chips and tasteless salsa, nothing. It was reminiscent of airport food in a place where nary a cactus grows.
We will not be back
.
