Ate here on our first night in Nashville after seeing it on Eaters 38. It was a great experience, but can't say it was the best of the trip. The broccoli was my favorite dish. The garlic sauce was SO good, it's a must order for garlic lovers. The duck, halumi, and beef dumplings were a bit underwhelming.  Definitely order the hummus :)

We thought we would try this place again after a year. Man...what a pathetic excuse for Mexican food. I mean....go anywhere in country and you'll find better food than Tito's. Florida, Chicago, LA. I was in Houston last week and couldn't believe how good the Mexican food was. It made me think about Tito's total disgusting food. Bad ingredients and poor quality meats = total shit food.

We have used BarkPark for daycare, check-ins, and grooming. All of the staff are very friendly, punctual, and experienced. I have two dogs with very different personalities (introverted + lazy vs. bouncing-off-the-walls crazy + outgoing), and they handle each dog exactly the way the dog would like to be treated! I am very excited to have a dog walker and doggy daycare center nearby, and I highly recommend them to anyone looking for reliable and excellent pet care.

I've been suffering from chronic back pain for most of my life. I lived a rough life as a youngster as a Marine, cowboy, investigator, skip tracer, etc. A broken and twisted pelvis combined with degenerative disc disease had me sleeping on a hard floor for 6 months.

I followed the advice of a friend and checked out Sleep Number. The salespeople were amazing and answered all our questions. It took a few weeks for our bed to be delivered but for the first time in a long time, I know comfort when I sleep and awake without pain every morning.

It's a significant investment, but one of the best I've ever made.

I hardly ever do fast food but today I was too hungry to cook so I drove over here for a quick bite to eat.  I walked inside and ordered my chalupa box with two frito burritos.  Those Frito burritos had the tortillas ripped up and served half open causing the insides to fall out of one and leak on the other. Would of been semi ok if all the ingredients were spread out but alas they were not.  My chalupa shell was served with undercooked shell and was very floury.  The service worker seemed pre occupied when I walked in, like I was an I inconvenience on their social life. Not a very warm welcome or meal
Amazing beautiful food. I'm addicted to their beef fried rice! They're always so nice and polite when you go there, I definitely a recommend this place

Service from Renata and Ken was phenomenal. Both made us feel very welcomed from the time we were first seated. Both were very attentive, professional, polite and extremely kind.

Food was really good. BBQ Shrimp was a good choice. Filet with Truffle Butter was a little under cooked from desired temperature but not enough to have sent back. Gumbo was good. Poached Pear Salad was very good. Pecan Pie was literally the best I have ever tasted! Chocolate Molten Cake was really good as well. I'm usually not a big fan of raspberry with my chocolate but this worked great. Royal Street coffee and cappuccino were both great. 

Great ambiance and location. Definitely recommend based on the great human beings, nice atmosphere and good food.

Basin is very good for brunch.  The food is awesome; the decor is jumbled up and average.  

Our party went for brunch. It was truly good, and we would recommend it to anybody. You could put this restaurant on the middle of Boston and it would be overrun. 

We had the fried green tomato eggs benedict, the basin breakfast and the chicken & waffles.  

One of us described the eggs benedict as "the best I've had in a long time" and as "designed to hit every pleasure spot."  

The Basin breakfast had several high points.  Bacon was grilled, so it was much smokier and juicer than most.  The boudin ball was crispy and flavorful, a great intro for the boudin-neophyte.  Scrambled eggs were plentiful, fluffy and swimming in butter.  Yum.  

Chicken on waffles is called "hot," but it's not Nashville hot.  Still real good.  Served in honey.  

App was the crab "biegnets."  Served in remoulade.  Very crispy and tasty. 

The drinks were well done.  Basin has a "bottomless" mimosa.  The Bloody Mary was as good as any I've ever ordered. Be sure to ask for it "topless" (with pickled vegetables heaving over the top of it). 

Decor is just muddled and odd.  You can tell they're trying to straddle restaurant and bar.  But it still didn't detract from the food.  Good New Orleans = probably some of the best food you've ever had if you're from anyplace else.

These guys were great.  The lady who scheduled the appointment was a little crabby at first so I was a little leary but the guys who cleaned my carpet made up for that fast.  My appointment was for some time between 11am and 1am and they called me at about 10:45 to check in and arrived promptly at 11:04 after I told them I was home.  They then proceeded to clean my carpet in the living room and the hallway which had some pretty bad stains.  I was afaid that I would have to pay extra for each of the stains but they quickly informed me that there would be no additional charge for each stain unless there were colors other than black revealed after the initial once over with the machine.  They finished up in about 20 minutes which I was a little worried about at first because I thought, "Hey I'm paying for this, take all the time you need, as long as you get my carpet clean and the stains out." but after they left and I allowed the carpet to dry (they said allow 2-3 hours for it to dry but I gave it 4-5 just in case with the windows open)  the stains (4 or 5 of them) were all gone and my carpet looked a lot cleaner.  I'm now going either barefoot or with socks on to walk around my apartment just to preserve the fine work this company has done for me.  All for only $60 !!!! Great value, just what I needed and expected.  Granted, I'm not a real connessuir of carpet cleaning because I very rarely have it done but they did exactly what I wanted (removed 4 or 5 bad stains that I didn't create) in a very timely manner and at a very affordable price.  Kudos to Jared and Lynn ?

Run-down location out in Temple Terrace. Dinner buffet on the weekends is $11.95 plus 15% tip for parties greater than 5. 

No fresh naan at buffet for at least 30 minutes. You can see the oil floating above the saag paneer. One server who knows nothing about the kitchen and didn't offer any drinks.

The only positive thing about the food was the chole. It was what kept from walking out.

Oh and a cockroach spotted near the kitchen

Recommendation: absolutely not!

I really have enjoyed living in this building the last few months, however the front desk man Jerome always seems angry and irritated. He's never smiled and will go out of his way to complain to you about something he seen you do via the cameras. I'd give 5 stars if it wasn't for that 


Update: Aimee reached out to me and I am confident she resolved our situation. Amazing customer support!

Gorgeous location.  Overlooking the Gulf of Mexico.  We all had the grouper sandwich with coleslaw.  Very good. The location was a little hard to find because the Bilmar seems to have both a restaurant and a cafe.

Always come here when in Reno.  Their  combination seafood pho is so good.  The broth itself is so flavorful.  Their combination fried rice was good too.  The host was friendly and took our orders right away.  I highly recommend this place.
Great new find for a vegetarian! Yay! A bit pricey for fast-food, but well worth it!

I would give it a 4 and a 1/2 stars but I can't do that on the Yelp App! This place was everything you expect at a quick bite to eat, restaurant. It has a great environment, amazing food, it was super fast and extremely friendly!! I got pulled pork and their cracked mac & white cheddar cheese. The Mac and Cheese was the best Mac and cheese I've ever had! It had Ritz crackers and white cheddar. It was delicious!!!! The pulled pork and sauces were literally something I have never had before. There was an apple oil & vinegar sauce that I think would of been delicious with a salad. The server was nice and extremely quick, it was like we were his only table. The environment was amazing! It was like a reusable, modern place and it was extremely well light which was something I'm not used to for a BBQ place! The only reason why it wasn't a 5 star was because the menu didn't have anything spectacular or unique to the place, although this has been an amazing restaurant!! 

Update: over a year later, I still think they have the absolute best Mac & Cheese that I've ever had.

Hadn't been to a Wendy's in a long time and unfortunately this experience doesn't motivate me to go back. While I never knew their spicy chicken nuggets had gone away, it was cool to see they were back in the menu. I hoped to have a positive nostalgic experience and at least a decent meal. 

Ordered everything on the mobile app. Got a double stack without the bun, specifying extra onions along with ketchup and mustard. Take a look at the attached photo to see what came out. 2 small bone dry patties, with nothing I asked for. 

Had I not asked, the cashier was also going to completely omit our drinks (2 frosty's and a Coke Zero) from the order. She also neglected to see the sauces that we asked for (the sriracha is lackluster according to my boo) and didn't put those in the bag either. Had I not been vigilant, what could've been a nice Saturday evening meal would've been without drinks OR dipping sauce. 

Fortunately we had ketchup and mustard in the fridge at home...

Not sure what the manager on duty was doing (I did see her there barking at employees). She should invest in a fly swatter, the place was crawling with em.
Great BBQ even better sauce. I would recommend the pulled pork. The bbq nachos are also a great choice!

Love this place! Stopped by for lunch on our way through town and couldn't be happier we did! Enjoyed both of our lunch choices; Anne's House Salad and the southwest wrap! Nice size portions and fresh and tasty ingredients! Wish we had a neighborhood place like this where we live. Staff was so friendly and welcoming. Will definitely go back again for lunch or even dinner.  Weekend specials and byob, which I always love! Can't wait to try again!

One of my favorite spots in St. Louis. There is a romantic and rustic ambiance to this place that I love. It's very dark and cozy with a nice candlelight touch. Service is always friendly and the bartenders take pride in their unique cocktails. Oh and did I mention the food is to die for?  A nice place for a romantic, splurge, forget-about-my-diet kind of night :o)

The pork belly hamburger is simply one of the best burgers I have had. Lovely pork belly on a hamburger patty (chuck, short rib, and brisket I think) cooked to order. Oh so fatty and tasty! The house fries served with side of some American cheese sauce blend is also delicious.

Didn't partake in the oysters or beer, so I suspect this will become my favorite place in the area.

Good service, didn't flinch when we asked to pay when the food came out as this was a pre-concert meal and we had to book.
The food is amazing here. Everything I've tried has been great and they have a lot of variety on their menu. Service is always great too. Nice addition to Magazine Street!

How fun! We randomly stumbled upon this Water Ski show and absolutely loved it. It has such a nice laid back atmosphere, everyone is super friendly when you walk in.

I have to give the performers a big applause, they do a great job. I like how the performances are all themed. We went for the 80s themed one and it was fun. 

Definitely come out and show your support. Show is free but bring cash to donate or buy concessions.
I tried 3 soups chicken noodle, kale sausage and velvet chicken. They were all excellent. I will definitely return when I come back!

I've been to Palace Cafe several times for business and have always enjoyed it. This most recent visit however was disappointing. We made a reservation and were seated at a very nice table. We were greeted right away by the drink server who promptly took our order. We waited a very long time to get our cocktails and in the meantime were greeted by our server. The restaurant was full but I've been to very few in New Orleans that aren't. We had been in town for a long weekend and had had our fill of seafood but started with crab claws and crawfish and brie au-grautin for appetizers, These both came out excellent and in very nice time following our turtle soup starter.  For a departure from the seafood we went with a filet and the duck with foie gras. By the time these entrees came out we almost forgot what we ordered. We also waited a very long time for subsequent cocktails. The servers were on top of the orders but the bar couldn't seem to get them out. When our entrees were finally delivered they were not even warm. The waiter apologized and immediately returned them to the kitchen. We then waited a long time again for the re-do. Unfortunately this time they were just lukewarm and did not taste right at all. After a few bites of her filet, my wife actually got sick and had been feeling just fine prior. The floor manager was very apologetic and brought us complimentary strawberry pie and took our entrees off of our bill. With the reputation of Palace Cafe I'm sure this was an unusual occurrence but for us an unfortunate final dinner on our last evening there after so many other excellent choices that we made the rest of the weekend.

Food and service are horrible.  Waited over an hour while many tables went unsat.  My fish was clearly something warmed up from the freezer.  I have tried this place for brunch, lunch, and dinner and all of them were horrible.  The live bands and scene is awesome.  I really want this place to succeed, but the menu needs a COMPLETE overhaul and improved service would be good as well.

Ate here a couple months ago once and talk about gross! The rice was totally mushy and disgusting. The service was slow and they were obviously under staffed. They were out of salad?? How are you out of salad? Not a place I would ever go again even if it was free.
This place is under construction, pool area is closed and customer service is awful. Should have stayed in airbnb. At least I have a beautiful view of the garage which is under construction! Yay!
Debated on going... just hate to go and find if the Jacuzzi being closed... the biggest is also being to hot out and waiting on the bus to get there... so.. ugh
The French onion soup is sooooooo salt! The reddish does not taste fresh. The taste of New Orleans is okay. The waitress does not have a good attitude. Do not recommend this restaurant.
There was little flavor to the dishes we shared.  It would be better if they cooked the peppers more to add to the sauce.  They should add some pizzazz.

There aren't many options at this casino and the menu is limited but the meal was still ok.  

I ordered their daily special which was black bean chicken over white rice with a drink and egg roll.  The meal was ok, not overly flavorful and exactly what you'd expect from a food court. I don't know why I went into it expecting a burst of real black bean flavor when all it really tasted like was sweet teriyaki sauce.  

Asked what the spicy Korean noodles were and it's just a Package of Shin ramen (that you can buy at any store for like $1)

We went here on a whim for desert. I had seen their menu beforehand and couldn't stop thinking about the warm Santa Barbara chocolate lava cake with Brazilian ice cream. Wow.. aren't you salivating yet? We didn't have reservations so we called to see if we could still get a table for dessert. The waitress said there were absolutely no tables and hung up on us. Rude. Despite the unfriendly first encounter, we were still enamored by the thought of the dessert. We decided to take a chance and walk over there. We got there around 9:30 pm on a Saturday and were immediately seated! There were actually a few tables open! 

The service inside was very good. Even though we just went for dessert, I had a taste of their warm bread.  Oooh, so warm, soft and not overly chewy. I have to say this is one of the best "table" breads I have ever had! 

Of course we got what we wanted: the warm chocolate cake. We split it between two of us..and it was plenty considering how rich it was. The cake was perfectly baked so the center came oozing out with melted chocolate. The ice cream was from McConnell's which is supposedly the best ice cream in town and beyond. It had the perfect amount of coffee flavor; not too strong and overbearing.. a perfect accent to the cake. I can't say this is the best lava cake I've had but it was pretty good.

Excellent seafood with great flavor and good service. Chris did a great job of checking up on our group and making suggestions. 

I really enjoyed the platter I got. Their blackened style seasoning on the fish, shrimp, and scallops was absolutely delicious. Their fries and onion straws were also very tasty. I think the lunch prices were reasonable for the quality and amount of food.

They have some decent daily specials and an amazing view of the water. I could see this being a good place to come for a semi-casual date night. 

Looking forward to returning to try the dinner menu!

Well we paId  for  the $18 pAckage the big package.  We paid for the mostt full-Service wash you cAn get.  We went through and there is a tavle with rags and spray botTles and so we went tO clean the inside. An employee came up and informed us we were not  allowed to touch them.   It was only for full serVice.   Ummmm we jUst paid for the biggest package yOu had.     Instead of arguing we left.   We won't go back!

Food was good and service was exemplary.  My son had a cheeseburger- medium - and it was perfect.  It came with fries and their homemade ketchup, which was really good.  Service was fast.  Highly recommend- will come here again.  Food was as good as their Tampa location.

Great atmosphere!
Really fun list of cocktails. Knowledgeable mixologist. My husband had their classic Manhattan, incredible. I had the Garden Hoe, highly recommend for a hot summer day. 
Definitely want to go back to try other cocktails and some of their tempting bar snacks.
The food was delicious and our server, Fernando, was outstanding! I ordered the cheesy shrimp and grips and is was very good. The hot chicken and fries was delicious too, as was the sweet tea.

The tidy boxes of buttons on the wall drew me into the Fabric Outlet on an otherwise frustrating day trying to find the right apparel fabric on fabric row. I bought some appropriate fabric there for an great price (honestly it cost half of what I'd seen elsewhere), and got some very unusual buttons.

I'm just learning how to make garments and choose the right fabric, and I must have gone into ten other stores on fabric row but they just didn't have the right selection of apparel fabrics (either very costumey with lots of sequins or completely lacking in non-upholstery non-quilting fabrics). Many of the other stores also smelled strange (musty urine scent), and were very hard to navigate with unrolling bolts stacked to the ceilings. By the time I got to Fabric Outlet, I was really overwhelmed and discouraged, but the gentleman at Fabric Outlet was very patient and I found all of the items I needed for my skirt class at Spool (even thread and invisible zipper). It was well-organized and had both a great variety of machine-washable apparel fabrics and some really beautiful quilting fabrics (I bought a Virginia Quilting Museum quilting cotton that I'm so excited to use later!). The selection is not huge, and I get the impression that it rotates frequently (it IS an outlet), but it was such a calm and easy to use change from the other jam-packed stores on Fabric row that I would definitely recommend it.

The worst buffet in Louisiana. The food is tasteless. Most items are cold. This use to be an amazing place to eat. It has been horrible for a few years. I have been warned not to eat there by several employees. They are correct.
Eric and Christin made our Sunday a Funday! Rocking this joint and the customer experience!

Another awesome dinner.

So, what prompted me to write an updated review of Da Sesto? Seeing a picture of Sesto holding a huge squid. No, hear me out. The last time I went to Da Sesto I tried the Misto di Pesce al "Jimmy V" con Fettuccine Integrale. I know, I absolutely adored the last pasta dish I had here, but I had to branch out and try something new. Man is that dish packed with squid! I kept lifting forkfuls of what I thought was just pasta and low and behold it would contain another ring of squid. I was in squid heaven. If you're a spice wimp at all, like I am, don't worry, it isn't a spicy dish, even though it is labeled "lightly spicy" on the menu. I'd like to think I was being healthy deciding to forgo a cream based sauce, so don't ruin my illusion.

My husband went with the Chicken Parmesan (of course it has a lot fancier title since it is in Italian on the menu) and loved it. Heck, I loved it. I kept stealing forkfuls of it from him. Luckily, he lost his voice the night we went, so I didn't have to hear him complain about my theft. 

We also managed to eat two servings of bread. (Why is their bread so warm and soft?!) 

Another fantastic meal at Da Sestos.

If you like being stalked by a salesperson this is the place to shop.  We were assaulted by a salesperson the minute we entered the store.  We explained we were just browsing in the hopes of making her go away but it didn't work.  Every time we turned around she was right behind us. It's a big store filled with unexceptional furniture so she did a lot of walking for no reason.  I would never buy furniture there.  The quality is suspect and I hate that style of furniture selling.
Love the Hamburgers. The sweet potato fries are delicious. Nice atmosphere and friendly service. Enjoy hiinv their. Ghd theater us awesome

Pandemic Review:
Orleans Shoe Company aka Good Feet has a new space on Magazine St. I tried to go to the old location (soon to be closing) around a month ago but found it closed; but maybe it should have been open? Anyway that location will be closed soon and this locations has 2x the space.

I can't even with normal shoes after this year so I was looking for baby feet size Birk clogs. And they actually had a pair! Yea. And the sales person was super nice and not pushy which is what I've always found with this shop.

Masks are worn by the staff and required of the shoppers and there is actually some room to move around so social distancing is actually possible.

I'm writing to inform property owners of my recent experience trying to rent from Prestige. I have an income property in another state and would NOT want a company like this managing it in my absence:

I recently moved to Tucson for work and plan to rent for a year while looking to buy a home. I am a single female college professor--quiet, excellent credit. I am the perfect tenant.

I viewed a townhouse in the Foothills and the location is perfect, the view is spectacular and the price is right. I want to rent this property! It is the rental of my dreams. However, it needs a routine between-tenant cleaning. I informed Prestige, in person with my wallet in my hand, that I would apply now and move in ASAP if they would have the place cleaned--specifically requesting that the carpets be shampoo-ed, the interior walls be patched and painted, and a couple of broken blinds be repaired (they no longer went up and down, so were not functional). 

The office staff acted as if I was asking something out of the ordinary, said they would "get back to me" if my requested repairs were going to be possible. I instantly got a bad vibe--as if she just wanted me out of her hair. So I left and waited, hoping for the best. After not hearing anything for several hours, I called to inquired whether my request would be granted. The woman I spoke to still had no clue if it would be possible--and didn't take the initiative to find out. Just said someone (not her, "someone") would call me back. It has now been 2 days without word, so I assume I'm out of luck.

I am not overly picky. When I viewed the townhouse, there was food remaining in the refrigerator and kitchen cabinets (it wasn't gross, just some coffee that got left behind), the carpets were dirty--had not been vacuumed so certainly not shampoo-ed, and the walls had many (not just a few--MANY) holes where pictures likely hung from the previous tenant. There were cobwebs on the ceiling and walls, which were several different shades of white and yellowish-white from different patchy paint jobs. The windowsills were grey with dust, there was soot in the fireplace, the air ducts were caked with dust (just the way they get when ignored--not a big deal to unscrew them and spray off in the sink), and I already mentioned that some of the blinds were not functioning.

If my tenants left my condo in this state, I would use part of their security deposit to have it properly cleaned. The maintenance I requested would run me about $400 in Chicago (mostly for the painters), so I imagine its about the same here.

As of this writing, the craigslist ad is still up so I assume the townhouse has not been rented yet. The owner has foregone income--plus the cost of utilities--that I was happy to pay.  I can only assume that Prestige is a slumlord company. My own experience, combined with the other yelp reviews here, give me enough pause to never consider renting with this company.

Update: the business owner responded and said they close at 11. We showed up at 9:30 and were very much unwelcome. Food was fine but I say skip.

We wanted to try this place since our Airbnb was so close but it didn't seem like the bartender shared our excitement. We showed up an hour and a half before they closed and she told us they were deciding to close soon. She was rude and everything she did she seemed like she would have preferred to be elsewhere. We even considered taking our food to-go so that we wouldn't bother them. It's a cool place but there is way better in New Orleans.

Gail knocked it out of the park! We needed 21 window coverings of various sizes. She came out the next day after we contacted her, measured all the windows, helped us select the perfect coverings and four weeks later they were installed flawlessly by her installer Steve. They hauled the old blinds away and we now have beautiful Hunter Douglas Duet coverings. I highly recommend Discount Window Coverings!
My wife and I loved it. Great lunch spot. Try the Italian cheese empanadas, won't be disappointed. The service was exceptional. They even gave my wife and I a free desert to share.

We love Isgro for their incredible canolis and the array of fresh baked pastries and Italian cookies.  They do lots of specialty bakery items for holidays like Easter and Christmas, and I know they get tons of orders around those times of the year someone plan accordingly if you are looking for a special treat then. Parking is a challenge and the inside Of the shop gets really busy during weekends and peak hours but it's always worth it.

A little often the beaten path of State street, the restaurant was a hit for the food and wine. We tried the free calamari app which was one of the good ones with fresh squid, light batter that doesn't seem greasy, and some good aoili sauce. The sea bass and cod were delicious and well prepared. The space is sleek and fun in the bar area especially for an off night. The service in the bar area was great especially considering it's only a year old rest.

It was okay, the air fried shrimp appetizer was amazing but the ramen was just okay. I never had traditional ramen before but it didn't do anything for me. The meat was fatty and it was mostly just noodles...not many vegetables. Meh.

I don't like giving crummy reviews. it doesn't feel good, and I don't like sounding whiny. On the other hand, if it means saving someone else from throwing money and time away, it feels slightly less whiny. 
This place is  mall food stand that is trying to present itself as better than just mall food. So my husband and I ordered Greek salads and our daughter ordered the chicken gyro with fries. $32 and 25 minutes later we got our food and sat down in the food court. ......twenty five minutes later. Was it crowded? No. Explanation for the crazy long wait? No. 
Our salads were fresh and tasty but they were floating in dressing. The chicken gyro was short on chicken, and the fries were seriously undercooked...they were raw. 
So...next time - It'll be back to Sbarro and a nice slice of cheese pizza for $3.99.

Had a superb cuban sandwich (not traditionally made i.e. not pressed but fantastic nonetheless), sufficiently strong coffee, and friendly and attentive service. Very good hipster watching and a rack of books to read to boot!

Very, very rude customer service. I've came here every year since living in Stl for my son's bday supplies but I will not go back. I was crouching looking at some balloons when someone comes up behind me and almost shoves me out of the way and I look up and its the girl thats working behind the counter. Try to order balloons and the man that helped us was also very rude and condescending. I will not give my money to this place again.

I have scheduled an appointment in advance over the past two months, and  have had to wait anywhere from 30 to 40 minutes before my services start.  My clue should be when the husband. who answers phone, and does not ask for my name or what services I am having done.  Another fun fact, pay attention to how they interact with their black customers.  They don't.  I have walked in and spoken to everyone in the shop on more than one occasion, and I have watched Stephanie completely drop head to avoid speaking.  Stephanie does my nails well, but she is not very pleasant and polite to the black customers.  The customer service at Natural Nails on Marsh Road is exceptional customer service to all races.  However. They don't do acrylic nails.  Thumbs down for niceness and friendliness to Stephanie at the Perfect Nails shop on Silverside Road.  Don't go there if you are black!!!  I watched the rudeness portrayed tonight to an elderly black customer and her elderly husband who came into the shop and he said hello, and no one that worked there responded.  Stephanie needs to go to a Civil Treatment or diversity class.

There are technically two Subways within eye range. Inside the shopping complex, there is a Subway inside the Walmart. A one minute walk in the same center past the Starbucks is this Subway. Service is okay; could do a better job handling when there there is a line to order and pay for the subs. Everything else is what you could expect from a Subway.

Wow, I must say I am totally surprised at how bad this place was.... it's a $150/night place running for 300-400 a night. 
Issues- no fridge, microwave (these were advertised as being in all rooms. Hotel undergoing renovation (not commented on) rooms STINK of paint/ammonia.... ice machine deactivated. Wifi only free if you have Hilton membership (which is free) 3.9Mbps download (not the greatest, barely enough to stream something) - it's a browser based access, so you can't hook your Apple TV to the tv here....

This is't a baaaad place, just that they charge a premium for... meh... you are waaaaay better off at Pacifica Suites, Best Western, or any other $150 / day ish place you find.... sorry. Hate that I paid for this, feel totally ripped off.....

This place is awesome for drinks and gatherings. Great for groups and great for separate checks. There is no table service only bar service. But there are plenty of bars so the wait is quick. It's usually very packed during games, so if you want a table, arrive early. Bring your dog! There are plenty there. I took off a star because the food just isn't that great. But if you want simple bar food like wings or burgers or mozzarella sticks, they've got you covered. Oh, and if you crave things a bit more fancy, the wine side has a bit better options. And awesome wines on draft. Mimosa buckets are only $22.

Love the hand grenade and thank you for the Skinny! Their other drinks are okay, but the skinny hand grenade is my absolute favorite! My husband loves the hand grenades too! This is our number one drink!

I was so disappointed by Emeril's Delmonico.  I had gone to Emeril's in Atlanta and was wow'd by the outstanding service & food so how different my experience at Delmonico was.  The service here was sterile.  The food was ok -- not great but then again, we didn't get steaks (which they are known for).  BUT if you offer a bunch of small & medium plates, expect that some people will skip out on the large plates.  I also thought it was strange that we didn't get bread service but everyone around us did.  The seasoning was off and I just didn't love the food.  I would definitely NOT go back if I were back in NOLA.  There are way too many other amazing places to go.

They butchered my nails! I went to get a color change and asked them to shorten the length a little. The man made my nails were sooooo short, beyond the tips of my fingers....way too short. They were on angles, the polish was is wearing off and its only been 3 days. Didnt use enough of the top coat. They try to apply as thin a coat as possible. I assume to stretch it as far as they can, but that doesn't work for me.  Never going back here.

The main attraction is supposed to be their beer. I tried 4 different kinds- and couldn't tell the difference. They're all super -sweet and very filling. One beer feels like eating half a loaf of bread! 
The food is okay but overpriced for what you are getting. It's basically the same thing as TGIFridays and Bennigans. So if you like that kind of thing- this place is okay. 
The atmosphere and service is standard for casual dining. 
The air conducting is awesome.
But the big downer is the only beer they have is their gross-tasting overpriced swill.
Amazing food! The service was also great! Highly recommend sitting at the bar. Chargrilled oysters were to die for!

I know this place is know for beer, but I'm not a fan of beer. I got cocktails instead, but they only have a few cocktail list. For the waitress to get us a cocktail list literally took 10 min. They had a huge variety in the cocktail list! I got the purple passion martini and the flavor was good yet not too strong. I didn't even get a buzz. 

In addition to the drink, I got the hummus entree, and it was delicious! They cut up an assortment of vegetables like tomatoes and olives, and the mixture of vegetables and hummus gave it a great taste! The pita was so soft and warm! And fresh! 

The environment is more on the fancy side. It has nice decors and good lighting. And the booth was very spacious-it could fit all 6 of us! 

Even though our waitress seemed busy, she was very friendly and suggested good recommendations! I wish they would schedule a few more staff during those busier hours.

UPDATED 7-25-08

Ok, so El Sol has good food.  I wouldn't ever dispute that.  BUT, the following things have recently made me have misgivings about this restaurant:

1. The East Washington location was closed for a long time.  Renovations.  I think it had to do with health department issues.  See my next comment.

2. One of the last times I was there, (summer 2006), I saw a cockroach on the wall in the entryway.  EEEEWWWW!!! 

3. Their margaritas are potent - I was always under the impression that they were made by hand.  However, last summer I saw them pouring my margarita - from a premixed bottle that is available from your favorite Costco location or local liquor store.  Talk about being ripped off - so I can't bear to order margaritas from El Sol anymore.

Since El Sol's Washington Street location wasn't open for so long, I made another good find with Adobo Grill's location on the northside.  That place frickin' rocks.  It's pricy, but delicious!!!

I'm that person that runs to yelp before making a choice on doctors, restaurants, dentists, etc! After reading their reviews I was very skeptical but after my appointment, I'm very happy with how my appointment went! It was clean, everyone including the dentist was friendly. After having a new dentist once a year, I'll stick with them!!!

It is one of the good Chinese places in Reno in my experience. That said, I should emphasis on "in Reno", where restaurants are not comparable to the ones in big cities.

***I know I probably should not do this, but I think the same owners own Taiwan 101 on 5th street. It is certainly worth going there. The food is good, the menu is interesting and prices are reasonable.

This is our 2nd visit to Another Broken Egg.  On our 1st visit I only rated them. 4/5. They more than made up for it this visit. This time we had the Supreme Omelet (5/5) and the Banana Nut Bread & Brie French Toast (5/5) which was OMG delicious! Regretfully I did not take a picture before digging in. It was soooo GOOD! Highly recommend and do bring your appetite when you visit. The servings are plentiful!  PS: they have the Best coffee cups!
Okay beer, my friend liked the blonde ...I got wine! Cute little brewing company! Would love to try the food next time!

I don't like buffet's,,,except for this one!

Great southern food in a old farm feel building.  Rocking chairs to wait in outdoors if needed. 

The buffet is always full of fresh foods like, fried chicken, pot roast, ribs, fish, mashed potatoes, fried green tomatoes. greens, corn casserole (awesome) fresh rolls and on and on and on,.. They also have a large salad bar, but I have to admit I go right for the main buffet so cannot comment on that. 

A server brings you whatever you'd like to drink (for an additional cost of course) and clears your plates as you run back for seconds, or thirds. Then on to the dessert bar where there is always a fresh cobbler or pie, cake, puddings and ice cream.  Ugh,, I'm full just thinking about it.

Prices are fair, about $10 per person (you have a few options on this depending on your appetite). Want a taste of the south?  Head to Fred's !!!

I love the Princeton location, so I decided to try here. Maybe it was just the time of day we came, service was very good, food was just ok. Atmosphere was kind of blah. Maybe if I went at night I would have a different experience. I will definitely give it another try, I really do like the food and the beer. The two locations can't be all that different right?

Romy Conley cooks up country comfort food and his waitress served it with easy-going southern hospitality, taking time to explain the menu. Conley had the tables repurposed from wood pallets which is homey, like the ambience in the remodeled old house in the Goodlettsville antique district. I took the servers suggestion of a turkey burger topped with cranberry compote, with a side of freshly-cut sweet potato fries. The sweet potato fries weren't quite as savory as Gabby's but were just fine.  Appetizer I loved was the Black Bean Salad with red peppers, avocado, roasted corn and pico de gallo. Best was the Fried Green Tomato with remoulade sauce. The waitress was so friendly, but I'm proud she didn't say "honey" or "bless your heart!"

this place is a welcome addition to renos food scene. i was pleasantly suprised at the ambiance,cleanliness and attentive staff.the fried yucca was amazing,the plantains and peruvian bean dishes were also very good.the chips and sauce were unlike any i had ever tried before. i ask everyone who complains about renos lack of dining choices to support el tumi and soon!
Very good but very expensive.  Small appetizers are in the upper teens. Average size entrees are in the upper 30s.  Good service.

We've lived in Franklin for almost a year now and we're still discovering new places to eat all the time. Recently on a day we both had off we were trying to find something to have for lunch, and since she loves Cajun food we decided to give Yats a try. 

The service is top notch. The guy at the register gave us a break down of every dish, and they let you sample anything you'd like. 

I ended up getting the drunk chicken and red beans and rice. My main complaint with most places that have spicy stuff is way too often there's too much focus in it being hot and not enough on flavor. There food here is a perfect combo of both. It's got some kick, but doesn't sacrifice the flavor. 

I'll definitely be going back again.

We went on Sunday, September 2nd.  I put our name in at 11:00.  I was told 35-40 min. for the wait.  I checked back right at 40 minutes.  I was told 20 more minutes.  The table was ready at 75 minutes, not even close to the estimated time!  We were frustrated and as we sat and waited, one worker was giving the hostess a talk for seating four parties before the party that was up.  She stated she was seating them by number and the table top size, so all the parties of four were being seated over other party sizes.  There were several online check ins that got bumped up, constantly, and it is unknown if the online check in was done prior to our arrival to make it not seem like cutting.  We passed on our table after feeling completely lied to.  I get it was busy, but being honest about an estimated time or even being close, or even sitting people in the correct order would be appreciated.  So needless to say, we didn't actually get to try the food.  We were turned off, and even more so when the hostess back pedaled and tried to claim we weren't told 35-40 to start with.  The parties after us were told 45, and I sat by the door.  I surely didn't imagine all these estimated times being stated repeatedly.  Needless to say, several parties left after their estimated time came and went and they'd go to the table asking how much longer.  I'd encourage you not to waste your time.  Parking meters are two hour max, a quarter for 10 minutes of time.  Or I'd suggest going when it isn't a holiday weekend.

More of a 3.5 star truck, because the actual Mac & Cheese portion of their offerings did leave much to be desired. But the service, insanely good toppings of decadence that they use to round out the portions, and fact that its the first mac & cheese themed food truck in Philly are all things that round it up higher.

From adding panko bread crumbs or corn meal crumble, to topping it of with bacon or BBQ chicken, and saucing it up with ranch dressing or parmesan pesto aioli; the things that you can customize your mac with definitely get taken a bit over the top. But hot damn does it deliver! The Cowboy Cup that I got at Love Park was fully loaded with corn bread crumble, ranch dressing, bacon, and jalepenos for that extra kick. And it loaded enough mac to encompass 2 meals! while leaving a bit to be desired, the 5 cheese blend (wish it revealed what cheeses!) of their truck was at least a filling result. 

With more varieties of mac to try, the sleek pink truck, and the prospect of getting a hot dog topped with mac & cheese; I'll definitely be back for more!

Who doesn't love a theme park? Theme parks are fun but they can also be exhausting. While visiting Tampa my family and I took my girls to Busch Gardens for a few hours. I don't even think we managed to get through the entire park. It was hot and honestly after we did all the kiddie rides we left. We were original suppose to go on a Saturday but it rained so they allowed my mom to move the tickets to Sunday. I will say they provide good customer service. However, their kiddie section wasn't that big and some of the rides were down. I understand some of the rides being down but the majority of them should be working of you charging people regular price. I feel if so many aren't working on a particular day, the price should be reduced for that day because essentially what are people paying for? The rides that the kids did get to ride they enjoyed. My youngest was too short to ride some of the rides but overall the girls had a blast! After so long, I think they were hot and we were all ready to go. Busch Gardens is a pretty big park. Like most amusement parks, be prepared to walk. The only other thing I did not like was the rides seemed so spaced apart. I know this may sound weird because you're thinking rides and they are huge, but something about the distance 3 rides took up/covered seemed off. Overall, it's a typical amusement park. I don't think it's anything special, but you can certainly have fun!

waited 45 minutes and observed how the employee spend just about all that time convincing a customer to buy the latest cell ... what a waste of time going to that store... my gear watch arrived via UPS to this store 6-28/2017 AT 2:32 pm, today its 6-29 /2017  8:23pm.,received by DAVID. HE DID NOT CARE TO CALL OR NOTIFY  ME THAT MY GEAR WATCH HAD ARRIVED at the store .. calling their # ( 813-252-5080  is a joke always a busy tone

I took my car in toe have the check engine light analysed.  My engine oil was 4 quarts low and I had metal to metal brakes.  They said they could not test drive it unless the brakes were fixed and the oil changed.  This is an older car and I did not want to put a bunch of money in it if there was something major.  So they fixed the brakes, changed the oil and did their initial diagnostics.  The oil change was over $100.00 which included rotating the tires.  I told them I did not need the tires rotated but they said it was part of the service and they just don't change oil unless you pay for the total package.So my initial bill came to over $800.00.  There conclusion was that the code came up saying I need 3 other diagnostics test done which will cost an additional $200.00 for total over $1000.00.  At this point I took my car back and still have no clue what is wrong with it.  When I take it to the salvage yard it will have clean oil and new brakes. In all fairness they took of the cost for the initial diagonals and we had a communication problem which contributed the situation.  I still have no clue what is wrong with the car.  One note is that there estimate for the  oil change was around $116.00 for changing the oil, rotating the tires and checking the fluid, etc. I can get the same oil change a Jiffy Lube for around $75.00

My husband Bought a fast pass to get the washers so he doesn't have to constantly put his credit card and he just bought a new truck and was told to transfer another sticker he would have to pay cash five dollars to the girl to put a new sticker on I think that that is absolutely ridiculous and it is not virtually spotless when your car comes out it is actually soaking wet and you're paying for nothing to tell someone you want to charge them five dollars to put a new sticker on when you're charging their account every month Is absolutely ridiculous because I bought a new vehicle my bank account did not change but was charged and they did not want to put on a new sticker bad customer service
Really solid sushi.  Hibachi tables are great for sake bombing.  Great atmosphere, highly recommended.

Was in town for business during the weekend and first week of their opening, my associate and I figured we'd check the food out since we'd been hearing all about it.
We actually ended up there a couple of nights, the food and ambiance was so good! It is a little loud, but that's to be expected when so much gorgeous wood is used in the construction and decor.
The bar design is unique and original, with the taps coming out of a maze of pipework like something out of a steam engine. The display case with their top shelf liquors is bright and tantalizing, and the dark wood all around is absolutely beautiful.
The service was excellent, even at a brand new restaurant, and the food...the food was outstanding. Definitely try the Smoked Mozzarella appetizer, the tomato jam they set it on is out of this world! And Fabio's Meatball pasta was to die for. Never thought of having fettuccine with red sauce, but it worked out just right.
Next time I'm in the area, I'll definitely be making reservations!

My wife and I decided to give the Screamery a try. I loved the ice cream, however it's super expensive. I know you pay for the quality but I can't justify paying that much for ice cream. If you are going to go for the first time I would recommend getting the sampler which give you 7 different flavors. They do unlimited free samples, but you can't stand there and try every type if there is a line. 

The employees were awesome and friendly. If you haven't tried it you need to. You will want to come back, it's just depends on how much you are willing to spend on ice cream.

My husband and I booked this tour based on the reviews we saw online and had to add one as well since this is one of the best tours we have ever been on.  William is an expert in all things wine so while you are on the bike he will fill you in on the history of the area and give you some really interesting background on the wine. 

The bikes were fit perfect to all of us.  There was another small group with us, a mother and her two adult daughters.  One of them is expecting and the other brought her small dog along for the ride in a backpack. William did a great job checking in on everyone and making sure the pace worked for all of us.  The area we went through was absolutely breathtaking!  There are a few stops along the way so that folks can take bit of a break if needed as well. At mile 11 there was a vineyard with wine tasting and the rest of our party decided to get off the bikes there while my husband and I finished the ride with William.  It was great that there was an option for folks to end a little early or continue on - highly recommend doing the entire 15 miles!

The bike tour ended in the small town it started at.  We did a wine and olive oil tasting there then we all went to another vineyard to enjoy and amazing lunch and had another wine tasting.  All 5 of us were going on and on about how great the day was, how incredible the lunch was and ways that we could help spread the news about how great the tour was.   

If you are reading the reviews and still unsure if you should do the tour - reach out to William (he owns the company and does the tours).  He will cover any questions or concerns you may have.  The girls did this and asked if they could bring their dog - turns out we have a dog as well so we didn't mind at all.  

I would 100% recommend this tour to anyone that likes being a little active, is decent at riding a bike and enjoys wine.

Holy moly!!!

Chef omelet I believe it was called. A giant omelet covered in chilli. HECK YEAH!!!!!

Cons....I didn't get to sit with my party and had to eat alone while they dined in another corner without me because space is limited. 

Idk if I particularly liked the waiter calling me beautiful every 5 seconds and constantly commenting on getting tips. Even worse than feeling harassed, was the fact that the compliments were so disingenuine. Every chick with a wallet was repeated the same line and all of a sudden became the center of attention when it was time to shell out.

Anyway. The price was great, the food was delicious and plentiful. Check it out :)

We had the best experience there. We where greeted right away by one of the nicest host.
Are server Drew was so accommodating to are needs as one of the persons in are party has special needs. He touched my heart how compassionate he was. The food was hands down the best I've had in Nashville.  The 18 oz. Bone in Ribeye is to die for. The only regret is that I can't give you more than 5 stars. KEEP IT UP WE WILL RETURN.

Obviously this joint has "big ass" slices of pizza (in a variety of delicious flavors) but what really impressed me was the friendliness of the staff. They were all polite and made casual conversation without being too over bearing. They made every customer feel welcome which to me, means a lot!
Just moved into the central west end and Have been taking my clothes here. So far so good
Great concept, sharing plates ensure everyone experiences the brilliantly balanced flavours and fresh local ingredients. Service from Suize was exceptional. Overall a A+ night.

Gosh, the cashier recognizes me now. Yikes!

I stop by every time I drive back north to Philly. Thank Buddha there isn't one walking distance from the apt or I might be in trouble.
This place is great! Food always comes out hot. The service tonight was great. Though it can be noisy at times. Try the beef tips with mashed potatoes. Don't forget the peanuts.

Went for dinner on a Tuesday night with two friends. Aps and entrees were delicious, as were pre-dinner cocktails. The wait staff was super accommodating and the (huge) gluten-free brownie a perfect cap to the meal. Will definitely be back the next time I'm in town.

FBY is by far the best barre and yoga studio in the city. The instructors are all very friendly, they teach wonderful classes, music is great and the environment is clean. I've been going to this studio for more than two years and I continue to feel inspired at the end of each class. Going to FBY is a must!

I just love indian food and this place did not disappoint. I've been there twice and ordered the vegetarian sampler both times. It's just so good and I love getting a variety of things. It can get really crowded so reservations help.
I ordered two Italian hoagies from there. The sandwiches were soggy and bland and the delivery was much later than promised. My recommendations are try someplace else.

My hubby took me here for Mother's Day Dinner.  We arrived early, around 4:30 and was seated right away in the bar area as requested.  There was some confusion as to who are server was, but did receive our drinks quickly and they were great.  We ordered the calamari as an app and it was good and arrived timely.  When we finally placed our entrée order, I had ordered the pork chops and was told they were out; in fact they were out of all pork items!  Really, at 4:30 on Mother's Day???  Instead I ordered the chicken piccata and my husband ordered the mahi mahi.  The chicken piccata was more like fried chicken with gravy!!  Not only that, I could barely cut it with a knife or chew it.  The mahi mahi was over-cooked and dry and the shrimp that came with it was the same.  We have eaten here several times with no issues, but we feel like Charbono's dropped the ball on this one.  Is it new management?  New menu?  Regardless, it was Mother's Day; any restaurant should know from past experience what you need to have on hand.

From a regular customer who even tips on takeout (never again): Food is good, but customer service needs improvement. The General Tso's chicken is usually at a 4 out of 5 level. The restaurant sent the wrong item for delivery and refused to provide any compensation for the inconvenience of waiting for a remake of the correct item, even when flat out asked. "Sorry, we messed up but we won't be doing anything about it." Incredible. They even asked me to return the item that was incorrectly delivered. Are they going to resell it? Isn't that a health code violation?

In town for U of A graduation and came here with a group of 12 to celebrate. We were not disappointed.  The service was excellent, never had to ask for anything.  Food was great with items I had never seen before. Shared the Cheese Curd appatizer which was light and very tasty. Ordered the Lobster Pot Pie which I would never have ordered but was recommended by our waitress. It was super tasty.
If you live in the area, don't pass up this place.

Discovered this awesome place a year or so ago. By far the best Mexican restaurant that we have ever been to. Wait staff is amazing as well. Definitely try the volcan, it is to die for (better share it with 2 others tho)

The location off the water close to the bridge makes its fun. We came here with a larger group for lunch and is a great atmosphere to watch a little football to have a good time. The food is pretty standard for a sports bar but one thing I loved was the chicken wings. 
Besides location and food the service could have been better. Overall looks a little under managed and there seems to be no sense of urgency with the servers. Ours I particular did not listen very well and did not take my boyfriends order. He sat while everyone around him received his food. After finally getting the order together they were nice enough to make it right to diffuse the situation. 
Kudos to them for making a bad situation right but would have liked it to be right from the beginning.

Found this place by accident when the restaurant we'd planned to go to was closed. We were drawn in by the smell wafting down the street and were not disappointed.

They serve tapas as well a full sized entrees that are packed with flavor.  I tried the lamb sliders, the Caribbean style shrimp and the crispy chicken tapas - all were amazing.  The jerk chicken over rizotto entree was something I never would have thought to order for myself, but I ate almost all of my boyfriend's plate!

Last thing I'll say is the service was great and the margaritas (with some kind of spicy salt on the rim) was the best margarita I've had in ages.  Great place, definitely going back!!

I came in for a haircut  and they are disorganized but in a quaint family-owned business kind of way. But overall Anne Marie and everyone else working there are sweet and caring and know what they're doing. I recommend this salon if you want a good haircut and aren't on a tight schedule.

I absolutely LOVE this bike shop. Not only were they accommodating when our family was visiting from out of state by providing us with bikes to rent and a bike trailer for our little one, they went above and beyond! We loved the bike trailer so much, we ordered one when we arrived home, not knowing it was curbside delivery only. Seeing as how we are over 1,000 miles away from their shop, the owner insisted he'd figure something out. I received a phone call 10 minutes later, stating they've express shipped my bike trailer, and we were beyond words. They have the greatest customer service, they went above and beyond, and truly CARE about their customers.

I really like this boutique on Magazine street.  Nestled in a row of newly rebuilt stores is this unique jewelry store which features an array of stones and materials as well as the ability to customize pieces to your liking.

There is a limited amount of parking in the back and you can also enter the store from that parking lot.

Kendra Scott influences come from objects and nature.  Her latest collection for the summer features beautiful pieces that range from tiny bracelets featuring Caribbean colors and vibe to large statement necklaces.

Prices range from $30 - on up depending upon the metal, material,  and stone(s).

The staff is helpful but not intrusive.  There is a constantly changing inventory of pieces and I suggest you go and visit somewhat regularly to see what is new.

The feature a few perks - one of which is a nifty birthday discount.  On your birthday (or very close - and yes - they require an ID to verify) you can receive 50% off one item.  That's a generous perk.

Check them out and just see if you don't find something you like!

The wait has finally ended. The food is delicious. These pictures will do it no justice. But don't take my word for it. Come stop by and try it for yourself. You will have a problem though you will not be able to choose what you want to eat.

I scheduled and arrived for my appointment for an eye exam only to be told the Lenscafters doesn't take my insurance.  I was surprised since my insurance is Blue View Vision from Anthem Blue Cross. I went home and confirmed with the insurance company that Lenscrafter and the optometrist who was scheduled to perform my eye exam do take that inurance. I further confirmed this fact in a later phone call directly with Lenscrafter. Apparently the desk staff there are poorly trained. As a result I wasted my morning with no eye exam completed. I'm now going elsewhere for my eye exam.

Solid ramen in my opinion.  Not everything is too my taste, wife didn't care for the spicy miso broth.  Daughter loved the pork confit.  Cocktails are basic and overpriced for what they are.  Will definitely go back though for the ramen.

This restaurant just opened, it may have been a couple of days too soon.  The food itself was okay, the sushi was good but the sushi roll I had was no more than average.  Service definitely has some kinks and the menu needs some reorganizing, as it's a little confusing.  We plan to revisit in a month or so to see how they are doing.  Although we didn't have the greatest experience we do realize  that there will issue that can be corrected.  Looking forward to having a second meal there and hoping they improve as time goes by.

By far, this is the best haunted attraction I've been to in Indiana, and I have been to just about all of them.  Themed, for the most part, not random from room to room with the typical characters.  Top notch costumes and props.  All of the make-up actors were cleverly face masked to not ruin the vibe.  From entrance to exit was just over 30 minutes.  I recommend the fast pass for an extra $5 and buying the timed tickets the day before, or early the same day you are going.

The Wait is over!
Having eaten regularly at their Food Truck and KNOWING they have the best Cuban, Deviled Crab & Empanada in Tampa (hell, probably the world) - I couldn't wait to eat at their new stand alone restaurant.
BOOM! LOVED IT!
When you go:
1) There is FREE parking in garage around corner from restaurant & a walk way through leasing center that takes you right to the street!
2) Lunch may be crowded, so try to go early (or later)
3) The Roast Beef Marsala may be the best sandwich in the world!
4) They have regular food truck items BUT have added a ton of new cafeteria style items (the Shrimp pasta was the best I have ever had!) and Michelle's Paella looked incredible!
5) They do serve breakfast as well.
For an opening day - it was packed!

Had sanitizer right outside so that's a huge plus for me. Ordered take out but had to come back. The girls were really nice about it and I found my food waiting when I returned. Ordered the crab sandwich which was pretty tasty but a little on the salty side. Crazy big portion of fries too but the cheese was very good. I can see where others would find everything too salty but have some water on the side to wash it all down and you'll be satisfied for sure. Had to save some for later because the sandwich and fries were enough for two people. Can't complain about this place but I can say there's room for improvement.

After spending $$$$ at the upstairs bar/restaurant I went downstairs to leave, after I stepped outside I thought I better use the restroom before the ride home. They would not let me back in because it was 9:03 and the were closed. WHAT???? The bar upstairs was still packed! This guy was very rude and not a compliment to their staff at all! This is to bad because one guy ruins it all for me, especially after I paid $18 for a glass of wine and $40 on 2 appetizers!  Will not be returning, too many other great places there.

These guys were awesome!!! My boyfriend and I were nervous about our move from our smaller two story town house in South Tampa to a single family home in Ruskin, but Viviane really put our minds at ease. The quote she gave me was spot on. The two guys arrived on time and gave me a 15 minute heads up that they were on their way, and even though they were young they were professional and worked quickly! They took apart furniture, wrapped everything, and got everything safely to the new house. Definitely would recommend to any of my friends who are moving!

I have traveled twice with Gate 1:  the guided 12 Day Classic South Africa tour and the independent 8 Day Barcelona & Madrid tour. The two trips were distinctly different but I was highly satisfied with both. Our tour guide in South Africa (Charl) was so knowledgeable about the country and really went out of his way to ensure that all travelers had the best experience possible. The Spain trip, on the other hand, was independent and did not have a tour guide. On this trip, Gate 1 booked the flights and hotels only. I have found that Gate 1 makes the booking process so easy and offers a great value for what you are getting. The hotels were very nice on both trips and I liked that some meals were included. I have been very satisfied with my Gate 1 tours and recommend them for booking memorable travel with a great value.

Just picked up my dog from there .. He was supposed to get a full groom .. They were grinding his nails apparently and the person doing it  wasn't paying attention  and his tail got caught up in the grinder and it  was burned pretty badly.. They said they couldn't tell how bad it was cause he wouldn't let them touch it .. Not sure what the hell kind of place they are running there, but we will NEVER take him back there ... My dog is in pain and needs meds all because somebody doesn't know what the hell they  are doing ... Never again !!!
This place is awesome! But, I'm really sad that they removed the vegan French toast from the menu.

After leaving Nashville for a year, I quickly discovered upon my return that Nashville is no longer "Music City" but has since changed its name to "Froyo City".  I think Froyo joints outnumber McDonalds and Starbucks combined in this town, now.  You can't walk a block without passing at least two frozen yogurt places (Please excuse my imprecise diction, but there really is no word to describe froyo "places". Coffee and espresso are at a cafe, ice cream at an ice cream parlor, popsicles at a popsicle stand, convenient items at a convenience store, steak at a steak restaurant, but what would be a fitting word to place after frozen yogurt? Oy, the dilemma of the English language). It boggles my mind that they all are still staying in business. This must only suggest that the average Nashvillian replaces one meal of their day with frozen yogurt. Seriously, people, the first step is to admit that you have an addiction.

Anyway, with that being said, I like Sweet Cece's because it's self-serve and has a variety of fresh fruit, candy, and other fun toppings.  The yogurt flavors rotate now and then but I am a personal fan of the Original Tart and also the Pomegranate Raspberry Sorbet (usually you can get these swirled together for an incredible combination).  There's always a staff member in charge of the yogurt dispensing machines, willing to give you a sample of any of the flavors before you make a decision. Although, they give you deceptively large buckets to place your yogurt in--I mean seriously, who can honestly eat THAT much yogurt?! (Okay, maybe I shouldn't have asked for a challenge)  

What separates Sweet Cece's from the rest though is the abundant topping selections.  Anything from cheesecake, blueberries, adorable mini gummy bears, other gummy phenomena, peanut butter chips, almonds, oreo cookies, brownies, and cereal.  Although, beware, if you get anything from the tall cylindrical columns, it will come pouring out before you know it.  My only criticism is that sometimes the fresh fruit isn't as fresh as I would like and I wish they expanded a bit more on this end.

The prices tend to be a little cheaper here than PinkBerry (but I do appreciate some of the offerings PinkBerry has over Sweet Cece's). They also have a frequent customer rewards card.  So, it's a good place to feed your froyo addiction.

I'm always trying to find a sandwich shop near my house that'll compare to DeliTowne or Braidos (my two favorite sandwich shops, that happen to be across town). I really wanted to like this sandwich shop, but it just didn't compare. I would say it's a solid 2.5 - 3 star shop...just average. I hate to say this, but I would probably pick Port of Subs over The Lunch Box if I was in the area.

PROS
- Local ingredients (or so they say).
- Locally owned
- Generous portions of meat 
- Nice array of toppings
- Great salad menu (I will try a salad next time and update my review).
- Good selection of bread 

CONS
- They were out of smokey cheddar cheese
- Inconsistent cheese slices (cheese was cut by hand and a bit too thick).
- Bread was a bit dry
- Burnt kids grilled cheese
- Pepperchini's were whole, not sliced 

NEUTRALS
- Average priced

Saturday evening we went to Calafuria for the first time.  Wow, the service was great, the meal was fantastic.  Two of us had Revoli, one cheese truffle and one chicken sage, the third had sausage , pasta and sauce.  Best Revoli i have had in a long time.  Wine list was spectacular and the wine my husband chose was outstanding.  All in all i give it a plus plus.  We are going back in a few weeks and i like that they take reservations.

We came in to eat at the new local restaurant. Knowing this place has tons of seating, I was surprised there was no waitress service. Also, this was a Monday night and we were the only ones there. We were told to stand at the counter to make our selections and read the menu on the wall. Hardly a way to greet customers!  I had children with me and all ordered something different. There were nothing but teenagers running the counter and food prep and no one seemed to know what they were doing, what ingredients some dishes had in them and they all seemed completely clueless as to what they were supposed to be doing! This place just opened within the month, it left a pretty bleak impression. Lastly, the food lacked taste. Awful. I work at two jobs, directly located across and up the street from here. I could refer them alot of business if I had had a better experience. Needless to say, I wont be back.

The hubby has been talking about this place for a few weeks, so we decided to stop in for lunch.  The salad was so-so, I mean, how much can you do with lettuce and veggies anyway?  Bill had the meatballs which were very good.  Juicy and tasty!  

There come the main course.  Makes me wish I had skipped the appetizer.  The strmboli was HUGE and oh so delicious.  I had to sneak a few bites when Bill stopped to breathe, which was not often.  I ate the entire bowl of stuffed shells although I was stuffed as well.  

All in all, it's worth the trip!  All I needed was a cot to take a nap in a soundproof booth to silence my snoring.  Be prepared to take some home as the portions are pretty big.
Food was just OK.  Service was adequate...frankly I prefer other local Italian restaurants.
I had the chicken salad sandwich with fruit- it was fantastic. Loved the patio, perfect for a lazy brunch!

When I went to Fast Smog, the attendant was beyond rude, barking out orders and cutting me off mid-sentence. The next day, I contacted the owner who seemed more concerned with how I got his phone number than the complaint I was making. He brushed off the issues I had by suggesting I was at fault by getting a smog check during a driving rain storm. I pointed out that rain didn't start falling until the smog check was half way done and he chuckled and said perhaps the attendant had a bad day. Bad day? The only way the attendant could have been ruder was if he had spit on me. Later, the owner emailed, demanding I remove my Yelp review because he had conducted a class with the attendant on how to deal with difficult customers. I declined.

This place is awesome.  In a world where there are a million "pizza joints" all doing the same thing, Commonwealth Kitchen has stepped it up with their menu.  I went with my family.  Totally kid friendly.  We had hoagies, burgers, and dessert.  I have to say all were phenomenal. EVERYTHING is homemade and fresh.

The poutine fries are AWESOME.  Anyone from NY/NJ would recognize these as gravy fries. Like I said they have all the neighborhood pizza place standards but turned up a notch, and they have kept the prices normal.  This place is brand new but it will be a NE Philly mainstay soon.  Awesome family owned spot.  Highly recommend.

WOW - this may be the best view from the downtown area! The JW is a staple of the skyline. The building is beautiful and you cannot miss the bar that juts out 34 floors up. Naturally we had to give it a try and I'm so glad we did.
 
I went up wanting to sip on a cocktail but am so indecisive. The bartender asked what I like and recommended a vieux carre. I've never had one before, but now I'll be looking out for this delicious drink! Subtly sweet and fully flavored, it tasted like a mix between a Manhattan and Sazerac.
 
The whole experience is just breathtaking. The atmosphere is so relaxing, the view is amazing, and the service is top notch. I cannot wait to come back for a meal.

I have mixed feeling about this place and do my best to articulate them clearly.  It probably helps that it's too early in the day to drink...so here we go.

Facility -  overall a nice sized facility with a wide variety of pitches.  Even on busy days, there's enough room to climb without having to wait for others to finish.  There's a 2nd level with simpler pitches that are good for beginners or little ones. 

Let me warn you that you are immediately hit with the overwhelming smell of stinky feet the minute you walk into the place.  I mean...whoa!  Outside of the assault on your olfactory senses, the facility is clean and tidy.

Equipment - the rental equipment isn't refreshed that often it appears and every time we've gone the equipment was clearly well used and marginally maintained.

Staff - very hit or miss.  Unfortunately, I've most often been met with the proverbial disenchanted millennial who makes you feel like you're sucking the life out of them just by being there.  

Biggest BS Factor - The $15 "belay lesson" is a total rip off.  The lesson consist of one of the aforementioned disenchanted staffers trudging upstairs with you to show you how to pass the rope through the belay device and keeping the slack out.  That's it - congrats, your done, now go conquer Yosemite.

To my knowledge this is 1 of 3 indoor facilities in the greate Nashville area and I'll be trying the others to compare and will update.

The food is reasonably good. You won't write home about the tacos, but you just might text your mom to tell her you found your new favorite locale. The staff is as friendly as the atmosphere is sunny. It's a great place to meet friends and enjoy a few tacos and drinks on the porch. If you're visiting Nashville and you're looking for a great spot to visit and take in the newly historic 12 south neighborhood without waiting for two hours or breaking the bank, this is your spot!
I been the last two day while I been in town and the food is so good !! Even better customer service!!!
Service was wonderful! Food was great, especially the sushi rolls! And they have some many gluten free options! I will go there again whenever I have a sushi craving!
First time in and really enjoyed it. If you're visiting Tucson definitely visit! Great Cuban tacos and the team is really nice.

We are serious fans of Indian food, but at this place we usually focus on the Nepalese dishes. Dal Bhatt is seriously awesome. Tse Phing (mung-bean noodles) are great. Hariyo Phulkopi (broccoli with cumin) we got the first time just to have something green, but it's now a staple. Helpful and friendly staff, especially once you level up by complimenting the Dal (which deserves every bit of praise - it's really different, with a fantastic mix of savory and sweet!). Only downside: wish that I liked the vegetable Mo Mo better, but they just don't do it for me; should try the meat ones sometime.

The doctor was kind and the staff was very helpful. My appointment was fast and they have the newest technology. I bought a great pair of Tom Fords. I will definitely be going back for my contact fitting too. Parking garage is close too.

The Tap Room used to be awesome.  Back when the prices were reasonable, the beer list had quirky (yet accurate) descriptions, and the owner cared more about supporting the neighborhood than stuffing wads of cash into his pockets.

The food is uninspired and routine.  The salads are downright disgusting. The waitstaff is moody and usually pretty slow.  The only reason the Tap Room is busy is because its the only bar in the neighborhood.

I recommend passing on this joint.  Walk a few extra blocks and you can find plenty of other places worth spending your hard earned cash at.

Awesome selection of beers and always good service. It's usually packed on the weekends but the servers are always polite. The bbq next store delivers to your table as well which is nice. I usually get a flight to try out new flavors or stay with the usual Hefeweizen.

For some reason every time we go her I spend way more than 
I  need to on great food items for the week. Also, sometimes parking is a problem on the weekends other than that great great lil shop
Just sat there for 25 mins and no one came over at all. Pretty sad. Guess I'm not cool enough for this place.

Been here numerous times, too many to count. While they don't have a good beer selection (iTap is next door) you can have them bring food to you at iTap. Pizza is a perfect NY style for sure...still doesn't beat the real thing. Sitting outside is real dope but they have limited seating. I'll keep coming back as the pizza is always on point.

Great food, amazing service, reasonably priced, with an incredible location. What more could you ask for?
A newer menu come Spring has new drinks, food, and twists on old favorites.
Chicken Fried Chicken was amazing and I highly recommend trying the Fire Chief Red Ale. 
You won't be disappointed!

West Park is off the beaten path. Tucked back in a neighborhood and flanked by Briley parkway, West Park is a relative unknown to many Nashvillians.

We have had some snafus; we played one of our games in the dark because no one was there to turn on the lights, several weeks the girls had to use the bushes as a restroom because the restrooms were locked. 

The parking is ample and the fields are taken care of. The grass around the fields gets a little crazy high sometimes. Not smokin. 

Overall, a nice hidden park for Nashville. Yet, leaving the amenities unavailable makes for some dark adventures with no TP.

The four stars I am giving Maynards are for the cocktail I had, a delectable libation combining crushed blackberries and whiskey. 

Potent, sexy and pretty to look at, it melded beautifully with the chic surroundings of Maynard's on a Friday night. Add to this a wild monsoon and you have a cinematic start to a night out.

The passing plates looked divine but I can't attest to their delish factor because all we did was drink. Next time Maynard, next time.

I had these guys to my house and was pleasantly surprised.  They did a great job and were very enthusiastic about getting the job done.
I expect to have them again.  They were very accommodating.

Great mexican food! Great green hot sauce! It's downtown, so the parking is tough during high traffic times. But you can order on their website which is a GREAT feature if you don't want to spend a long time down there. I do like the outside seating because the sidewalks are wide and you don't feel like people are shuffling past you. Inside seating is fairly large, but this establishment is best for a quick eat or an order and run. But there is a fair amount of space.
