Great food, great fun and great people, all I can say. The bartender was amazing, I think her name was Kirsten. She was for sure the highlight of our trip for my nephew's 16th birthday dinner!

Ashley Zachary at Stout's is wonderful! I strolled in on a rainy day just to browse for some practical flats, which turned into flats plus an irresistible pair of colorful heels. I always assumed I couldn't afford Stout's for some reason, but after my visit I have realized that is not true. My flats were the exact same price as I had seen on Amazon and Carson's. 
The nice thing about Stouts is the sales people know their shoes and can provide helpful suggestions and details about shoes (i.e. where their made, materials used, and design benefits). Stout's has a wide variety from hiking shoes, to Danskos, to fashionable heels.

Went in for dinner last night for some good food and some good music. Unfortunately the DJ who is just awful switched from some decent toe tapping funky music to full blown 'techno rap'. There were six of us and we cancelled our apps, finished our cocktails and went to Circles. We saw probably another 15 people get up and leave at the same time.  Ownership, I think you need to understand your demographics or your Saturday nights are going to rapidly drop. You're a beach bar for goodness sakes. Come on!

This was such a trash experience. We signed up for the Voodoo tour thinking we would get more of a lesson on Voodoo and it's influence on the history of New Orleans and the French Quarter and instead we got one and a half hours of talk about how different family members of the tour guide had been hexed and how "we celebrate everything in New Orleans", "this is how we do in New Orleans", and what different households did for Mardi Gras since it was cancelled this year due to Covid. I immediately regretted the decision to sign up for this tour the minute our guide started talking. Overall it was a waste of time walking in the extreme heat for nothing. The highlight of the tour was going to Marie Laveau's house at the end of the tour that took all of 10 minutes, which is now being lived in by two different families. I would never recommend this tour to anyone. You'd do better researching online yourself. This was a terrible waste of time.

Amazing music club.  Not much seating. Be prepared to stand or dance. 

Excellent music and there is live music the entire time its open(besides set breaks).  Beer prices are about $5/bottle and no cover(at least when I went) so its reasonable. 

I'll be back during my next visit.

Goody Goody is a great atmosphere with good food to boot. If your looking for a blast from the past that won't miss on good homestyle food I would definitely recommend. 
PS: I would suggest the milkshakes.

I've gotten my lashes done twice by Ally and she's amazing! She's fast in her application but precise. My lashes lasted 3 weeks and I honestly could have gone longer without a full. I get the "full glam" look at it runs $75 for a fill. Worth every penny!
Breakfast was great!  Best pancakes I've had in years, this will be our breakfast spot for the rest of our vacation.
Yummy! I have been waiting so long to try this restaurant and it was well worth the wait! Everything was tasty, the service was excellent.  I will be going back!

I should post more reviews because the Peppermill has be good to me and my company off and on for years. But on my last visit it took 65mins to get a drink at the Terrace lounge. The room on this trip was not up to Peppermill standards the shower cap box had a packet of sugar in it and the bathroom had the last persons soap left in the shower. Over all I was not pleased on this trip
Expectations were luke warm. Wife booked a walking tour. Grabbed a cocktail and a cigar for good measure. Jonathan instantly changed the mode with his knowledge and enthusiasm. Truly enjoyed it.
This place is wonderful. Their baked goods are excellent, try the bread pudding. The sandwiches, coffee and service have always been excellent.

I am very impressed by the service at Havertys. I specifically went with Havertys over another big name store because they were able to  guarantee delivery is a short amount of time which was very important since I was moving to another country in a couple weeks. The delivery window was 2 hours rather than 12 like me other places. My furniture actually arrived at the top of the delivery window. I also received a handwritten thank you note from the sales person as well as a follow-up phone call from him following the delivery. Havertys has top notch service! I will definitely recommend them to anyone looking for furnishings.

I haven't been there post-Katrina, but I'm not going to lie to you.  Their Freret St location was sketch.  I was a little nervous.  Good thing they've got good, home-cooked, Southern comfort food.  Go there on Monday's and get their red beans and rice with fried chicken.  Damn DAMN good.

This was our favorite part of our New Orleans trip. Jonathan is so passionate about his tours and gives you the real deal.  We did the dark history tour, and we were sad we didn't get a chance to do any more of his tours. Next time we are in New Orleans this is definitely something we will do again. I couldn't recommend it more !

This will be my next go to spot! They have a huge menu to look through, but our waiter pointed out some popular items on the menu. His suggestions did not disappoint. They have a great kids menu as well, and the portion sizes are very fair. They have a vast selection at the bar as well. Also, I should add that the wait time wasn't bad either. Give them a try. Thanks Greg for the awesome customer service! 

P.S. pricey but worth it.

It was $20 round-trip to NYC from Philadelphia. Clean and comfortable bus. Left on time and arrived early. WiFi didn't work, but it doesn't work on planes most of the time. I'll use Megabus again and recommend it to friends.

Arroyo Burro Beach is VERY dog friendly. Make sure you check which side of the beach you are on before you take off the leash from your dog.

Parking is free at their lots (there are two) but the place is popular and fills up early in the morning.

Doggie showers available. 

Very nice restaurant present for your beach-side brunching needs. I know: very first world problem-- "brunching need". 

Outdoor shower to wash off sand at the end of the day.

Shallow tide pools present.

Long and narrow allows for a very nice run. And while you're running, you can look up at the Cliffside homes and marvel at some of their landscaping.

I've never seen this truck before today and decided to give it a try. I bought a piece of the butter pound cake and it was really good. A true acid test for a great cake is a moist bottom and this cake has it. The entire piece from top to bottom was consistently moist and fluffy and was very nice. That said, the cake was a little too soft to be what I know of as a traditional pound cake (which is a lot more firm). It's more like an egg cake. Whatever it is, it's a nice piece of cake and I will surely stop by again if I see this truck!
This place is awesome. The owner is very friendly; the bagels are soft and flavorful. Good coffee, good atmosphere and good food! Would recommend to anyone!
Chicken is very juicy. Sides are great. Local beers on tap. The Damn Hot chicken really is Damn Hot!
My family absolutely loves Desert Sky Spine and Sports. We get the very best care here and highly recommend it for any therapies, injuries or general needs. The staff and doctors are fantastic!

We are regulars at gcfb. And mug
Club members! I am consistently pleased with the food! We have our favorite servers (you can't go wrong with Christina or Andrea!) and favorite meals (boneless buffalo wings or the tomato/bacon flatbread!). The beer is awesome (try a two pull!)

5/4/14
Updating & lowering 1 star. Prices have jumped $1-2 on sandwiches in the past few months and the price vs food quality isn't as high as it was. Disappointing but a fact of life I guess.

My girlfriend and I had an absolute blast!! The teacher was very patient, considering that we have no talent. I loved the suggestions they offered, pictures they took, and music choices offered.

I felt that they were very customer service oriented and friendly. I've recommended this to several people and next month, I'm going with some more friends. Very much looking forward to it!!

Found this place on a food blog and I was curious, so I tried it out. I'm pretty big fan of fried chicken and I don't get to try places that specialize in fried chicken very often.

Pretty difficult to decide what to try here. The fried chicken pieces, chicken sandwich, and the chicken tenders all looked good.

I tried the chicken tenders and the tots. The chicken tenders were very good. They were lightly battered with a hint of honey flavor. Not over fried or soaked in oil. The chicken was tender and flavorful. The tots were pretty much standard.

Definately going back to try some of the other items.

One note. The online ordering estimate is pretty accurate. Everything is made to order, so the wait times can go pretty high during peak hours.

I've used Impact Carpet Cleaning several times at two properties. I have two pets and a baby, so clean carpets and furniture are a concern! Jerry is fast, friendly, and does a great job for a fair price. I would highly recommend Impact.

I love this place I always order on mondays when I work all day. The food is fresh and responsibly priced. The delivery comes earlier than expected and the gentleman is so nice. Wont go anywhere but here.

I wanted to give a shout out to Anna's nail salon. The staff is always accommodating and delivers a great service. I get it I am a man but nothing worse not have clean nails on my feet and hands... Thanks always for the kind words and I'll see u soon

PEGASUS 2.0 is better than ever!!!

Pegasus is back with all your favorite DJ's and bartenders and the new place is nice and clean! 

Monday night is 80's night.
Pornoke anyone? Come in and keep the legacy alive. They desperately need a sound system upgrade so come in and spend some money!!!

NEVER STOP GOTH POPPIN!

Walked in to West Elm with the intentions of buying a coffee table my girlfriend & I both liked from a previous visit. I just needed to confirm the dimensions and get some questions answered regarding shipping; an the current promotion they are running for the holiday weekend (Cyber Monday to be specific). Well after walking in and inspecting the table, measuring it myself with a measuring tape I looked around for a sales associate to answer a few questions. 

5 minutes went by no associates approached me despite there being several (I counted 4 female & 1 male associate) in the immediate area. I tried to flag one down but they seemed far more concerned with chatting & rearranging the store than making a sale. Now a little annoyed I decided to make a lap around the store in hopes of getting the attention of someone interested in selling the furniture in the store. After completing a lap i returned to the table, waited another 5 minutes with several associates walking by but never inquiring if they could help. 

I'm sorry but at a certain point it becomes about the principle of providing basic customer service.  I'm not going to chase down folks whose job it is to sell & assist customers so I can have the privilege of spending hundreds of dollars in their store. I won't be spending a dime at the Hyde Park West Elm, they have plenty of competitors who make equal or better furniture who actually give a bleep about their customers.

The best part was the first interaction I got from a associate was on my way out as the cashier wished me "have a nice day". Maybe they should let the cashier run the sales floor.

ditto what most others have said...intersting and diverse clientell....that is if your idea of diverse is chain smoking maniacs....terrific bartenders...good beer/drinks...prices are nearly free....but...some service issues on the floor...and the smoke is rediculous

The music has been quite a mixture...although I prefer the punk and would love to hear more of it.

Service is pretty good at the bar....abosolutely and unacceptably horrendous on the floor....mind you I have always sat at the bar...but...as a former "turn around" specialist for chain bars/hotels....I tend to observe from afar....water glasses nearly always empty....servers never looking in anyones eyes....condiments not dropped off prior to food delivery....no extra napkins with obviously messy items.....servers yapping/smoking to each other at the bar when they should be landing at their tables....its great to hire your friends...but...this staff is in desperate need of some very basic training.....i.e....I don't want to see you put down a lit cigarette and carry food to your table...disgusting.

Bartenders are quite good and very friendly....great revolving beer choices....food is pretty darn good...and more importantly..not fresh off the food service truck......although kitchen can be slow....and I have had the kitchen guy deliver my food to the bartender whilst clutching a heater in his chops......ummm...thats disgusting...

I like the wide open space....but the odor of smoke and whatever else is disgusting....they tell me they spent 30K on some smoke eating/fresh air machine as part of the HVAC system....might think about getting your money back....

I just wish one of these bars would see Radio Radio's success and try non-smoking....you won't lose your smokers...and you will gain the non-smokers...who....tend to be more affluent...with higher ticket totals...better tippers...although they don't tend to go out as often as smokers..

Hope this place continues to be a success....and I would be there damn near every day if they would go non-smoking....c'mon legislature...welcome to the new century of enlightenment....where everyone understands second hand smoke KILLS people !!

Also..this place is local...spend money locally !
Tried Fish and Chips as my first experience at Nikka.  Price matched quantity, though quality could be better.  Taste was a bit bland.  Might try some other dish, then update.

INCREDIBLE! 
This is some of the best chicken I have ever had. It is always perfectly cooked and seasoned. The seasoning is one of the most unique flavors I've had. I crave it often. 

The staff is super friendly and will let you try things. Super affordable and healthy. 

I CANNOT RECOMMEND THIS PLACE ENOUGH!

This is an all around nice place for brunch or breakfast. The service is attentive and quick and friendly. The food is good, probably even better if you try the specials rather than sticking to traditional stuff, which is still good. Lots of people mention the free coffee outside as you wait, but it is terrible terrible coffee. Given that that's the only downside, a great place.

I'm not one to make my reviews into novels. Here's what I think:
This is a solid restaurant. The food here is very good. They do close for lunch, so if you go after lunch has ended but before dinner begins, you have to eat in the bar area and the food menu there is limited , however they do have the "red fish with lump crab" on the limited bar menu which is pretty much amaaaazing. I highly recommend it. I absolutely will go here again.

Solid.  Everything we got was good and the had a nice beer selection.  I got a bbq sandwich that wasn't severed with a sauce (which I think is one of the 10 commandants... "thou shall serve bbq dripping" and one that I generally live by) but it was spot on.  The meat wasn't dry at all.  We brought our 1yr old with us to lunch and they were very accommodating as well (especially for a "dive bar").

My roommates and I have very little self control and live within walking distance, so it was only a mattter of time before we got there. They close kind of early compared to other places in Grad Hospital, so it took a few times of trying before we made it while they were open. Enabling each other further, we each got one regular sized jar ($5) and one small size ($3.50) to try more flavors. I got the banana cake with cream cheese frosting (divine) and the birthday cake (adorable, but the sugary frosting kind of washed out the flavor of the cake). My roommates got the carrot cake and some gooey caramel chocolate cake (she forgot the name) and they loved those. And, we were told, if you bring the jars back you get 50¢ off... considering how often we crave desserts, it'll be soon.
Great portion. The omelette is enough for 2 person! Quick service and welcoming. Pity there's not a lot of bacon in our eggs for a bacon place.

I stopped going here in the last year! I live in newtown so the drive wasn't bad.  But the size of the orders got smaller and smaller! It was almost a joke! Over priced for where it's located. The bathrooms are always dirty. And for some reason the parking seemed to always be an issue even though the place didn't really seem that full! I would pass on this place!

Absolutely no customer service and the longest, slowest checkout lines.

They shouldn't have bought out the Vons. 
I will DEFINITELY not return.

I'm so excited that I've found delicious Mexican food that my partner and I can agree on! It's so good!!! We ordered takeout one evening and while the wait was a little longer than we'd like, it was worth it. I can't wait to try more dishes. We got the chips with guacamole and salsa, cheese enchiladas with mole, and tinga enchiladas with verde. The guacamole was some of the best we've ever had. The chips and salsa were also good. Both enchiladas were thoroughly enjoyed. I'm always looking for the perfect mole and I think I found it! Such a great balance of flavors. The cheese in the enchiladas was melty, which seems rare. The beans and rice were also super flavorful. In addition we tried the horshata which was decent but had a little too much cinnamon. I will be back for sure!!

If I could give 0 Stars I would, what a nightmare.  I had my entire AC system done by AirZone and they failed to pull a permit, I had to call the building department and then after 4 months they finally pulled a permit.  Then its been a year and now my AC has leaked through my ceiling and ruined my attic and ceiling!  I called them about coming out to look at it and they refused.  I had another contractor come out and look at it only to find out AirZone did not "hang" the handler as I paid for, they have it siting on my beams, they melted an OLD PVC pipe to bend it NOT replace it as I paid AND it states in my contract AND the unit is out of Plumb and is now BENT! They are not willing to take any responsibility for the bad installation per Sean who I spoke with about the issue.  I found out by hiring another company to come check what was going on and they would not even touch the work because air zone CUT MY SUPPORT BEAMS in my attic.  They have not taken responsibility at all and now I am having the City of Tarpon Springs building department re open the permit because I cannot risk the ceiling falling in.

We came here Monday after going to the Andrew Jackson Hermitage Museum, which by the way was very good and informative. We took a few minutes to have a look at the menu, which had a lot of options for everyone. I ultimately decided to go with the Pour House Burger, which was an interesting twist to a burger. It had fresh avocado slices, and an onion ring. Very nicely sized burger, and cooked to the temperature I like. I got a side of tater tots with it, cannot ever go wrong with tots. Reason I am giving it a 4 is because the service was a little slow, but that is also on the management team. She was running around the whole restaurant as the only server, and you had one bartender too. It looked like I only saw two people in the front of the house the whole time. 

Definitely recommend this place to people, but hopefully you don't have just one person running tables when the Titans start back up!

I took my wife to the recently opened Adryana's Latin & Italian Cuisine right in downtown Plant City.  I had seen really good reviews of it on FB and wanted to take her someplace nice and different to make her birthday dinner special. It was a tremendous success. First, the decor is simple, but very refined. They also had a gentleman playing the electric violin and that was a sweet edition. He wasn't playing traditional classical music, but more contemporary classics on it. He was really good and that added to the ambiance. Our water was spot on with service. They were doing a date night special, which was a really good deal for 40 bucks, but we decided to stick to the regular menu.  My wife ordered the Fried Pork Chucks which are center cut pork chucks marinated in Mojo sauce and fried with fried green plantains. It comes with Caribbean Aoli which was a perfect combination. The pork was very tender and seasoned well. I ordered the Shrimp Trio, which is a combination of Shrimp Scampi with pasta (probably the best I have tasted of this dish ever), fried shrimp, and Cajun shrimp. The fried shrimp were barely battered and fried without being greasy at all. Perfection!!! This was a tremendous amount of food for the two of us and we will have left overs for at least another meal, maybe two. 

During the visit, I checked in on FB and it was only a few mins when the owner came out and wished my wife a happy birthday. He was very cordial and even brought her a piece of Sweet Berry Cheesecake. 

This is a wonderful addition to Plant City, as there is nothing else in town like this.   We will definately be back.

We stopped in to day at around 11AM for an early lunch. The woman behind the counter (where we decided to sit) took our order. As we waited about 20 minutes we noticed other guests getting their lunch that came in after us. We asked our server about our order and she gestured to the kitchen like it was an error on them. Since we were sitting at the counter we were able to watch the cook. He never received our order to begin with. She took our order but she never put in our order! We decided to leave, not even an apology on her part. 
Very bad customer service on her part, she needs some training in better behavior to guests. We have seen her before, we are repeat customers but not anymore!
I come thru Tucson a couple of times a year and stop here if I am around. They never dissappoint! Great sushi, reasonable prices, and super friendly staff!

I stopped in with my boyfriend on a whim on Saturday afternoon around 4 p.m. upon walking by and noticing the sign out front advertising "pizza and beer flights" from 3-5 p.m. on Saturdays.  The bartenders greeted us immediately and we took a seat at the end of the bar nearest to the kitchen.  I didn't see the upstairs of the restaurant, but the downstairs is bright and airy and gets lots of nice sun through all the side windows.  The staff was also very friendly, which we appreciated.

We opted for the specials, which were $2 off either flight on the menu (American or Italian) and a margherita pizza for $10.  The pours in the flight are generous, and the selection of beers was great.  I can't speak to anything else on the menu since they were not serving anything other than pizza until 5, but we had a positive enough experience that I'd consider returning for dinner in the future to further explore Brigantessa's offerings.

Listen, and listen well. Do not eat from here. This place is unsanitary and should undergo an inspection from LI. So I ordered a small pizza from here and apparently a bug was cooked on the pizza. Unfortunately I didn't notice until after my daughter and I had two slices.

Also, two months ago I ordered a cheesesteak and they sent me someone's order (a hoagie) and tried to give it to them. I called the other customer to make them aware of the mixup and to ensure they got a fresh order despite me not doing anything to their food. Short story shorter, they were trying to give the other customer the food they gave me and I opened.

You've been warned.

A bit of a mixed review because the hubs and I differed on our opinion. We agreed on the fact that it is always a bit unsettling when you are the only ones in the restaurant. But I will attribute that to the reality that it was a Monday evening, and it does seem that Royal Thai is more of a business lunch kind of place. The restaurant was clean and elegant and the menu was extensive, with pictures of almost every dish. The staff was friendly and the wait time to get food was normal. If I had any complaint there, it would be that my food came out about 5 minutes before the hubs' - which is a bit of a pet peeve. 
I chose the garlic prawns and sea scallops which was underwhelming. There was little hint of garlic, the portion was small for the price and the steamed broccoli upon which it was served was only lukewarm. 
The hubs had a great meal, however. He ordered the lamb shank which was served with potatoes and onions smothered in a slightly spicy curry sauce. He proclaimed it some of the best lamb he had ever eaten. I sopped up some of his sauce with rice and it was bold and flavorful. 
I'd give this place a second chance because there were tons of options and probably better choices to be made.

Delicious, healthy and fresh!  They were literally cutting the onion slices off the onion for my sandwich as I stood there!  That said, be prepared to wait a few minutes for to-go orders!  The fresh ingredients explain the prices (with tax my veggie sandwich came to over $10).
Carmo has ample seating and a menu of fresh items that changes frequently!  Everything sounds and looks so delicious, it was hard to decide what to order!  I would strongly suggest for a quiet little lunch if you want to sit and relax while eating healthy and hearty!
I look forward to returning and trying so more menu items!  They also have plenty of veggie and vegan options and a SUPER FRIENDLY staff!  I was also pleasantly surprised to find ample street parking and its within walking distance for anyone working downtown/CBD!

People aren't really helpful. Wandered around for awhile and no one even made eye contact for the first 5 minutes. The few stars are for the guy who actually attempted to help, he was ok but shot my dreams of a new phone down pretty harshly to go back where he didn't need to deal with customers. No one goes into the phone store for funsies, so when the customer service is poor it makes the whole experience even more miserable.
Decent food, great salads! Excellent happy hour! Friendly service, waitress tried super hard to make a birthday celebration special! Yummy desserts!

Good service, but food was super gross. I try to make it a point to try eggs Benedict at any new breakfast place I visit. This was the worst I've ever had. The hollandaise sauce was seriously heinous. The country potatoes on the side were mushy. My companion was similarly unimpressed with his biscuits and gravy. Not a place I would return to.

I was treated here for back pain from nov to dec of last year. This clinic is really great. Ive been to 3 other PT clinics over the years and this one is definitley more hands on that other places. My therapist Sarah, would go up and down my spine mobilizing each vertebrae. That, coupled with heat, electical stimulation, and a home exercise program had me back to running without pain.
For great food and service this is one to go to regularly.   It's a small restaurant tucked in a strip mall that's a delightful find.
Went here for dinner and what a great experience.  The drunken shrimp were out of this world.  Service was great and nothing like having fresh fish caught a matter of hours prior.  I'll be back!

Except for the wedge salad and Ceasar everything was average and way expensive.  It is high end pricing without high end quality.shrimp in shrimp cocktail overcooked.  Coffee soaked filet tasteless actually.  Add au gratin potatoes which were dry and two drinks and you have $118.00 bill.  Service was exceptionally good.

A couple of my friends work here at cadia pike creek. I know every nursing home has there own problems but I was told this place doesn't work with your schedule They've told me horror stories about people showing up to work and walking out because of how incredibly short they were. My grandma was also a rehab resident here and she told me how during one shift she hadn't been changed for four hours. From my own experience, of me seeing her there, if you want quality service do not send them here. How can you expect quality service if people are upset or always walking out. They give 3-11 pm aides 16-24 patients depending if someone doesn't show up for work. How can you expect people to get changed, showered and put to bed? The Human Resources including "Director of nurses" claim they care about there staff when in reality if any shift is short, they go home. You would think they would stay to help but no they don't. you can complain all you want. Unfortunately nothing has been done yet. Stop offering sign up bonuses and just shut the place down

Why is such a nice-looking, well-designed downtown space empty on a Saturday afternoon? Perhaps because it is staffed by a pair of posers who sneer at dark roast and then charge $4 for a bad-tasting cup of attitude. I had brought a buddy from out of town, hoping it would help to elevate his impression of Tucson. Fail. I'll stick to Luce and Time Market.

I believe there was a switch in management here because the owners are a lovely adorable couple!

I bring all my alterations here and they are very responsive. Most alterations are fairly priced for South Tampa. 

I brought my Vietnamese tea ceremony dress here and she was able to hem the bottom even though there was a delicate overlay on top! She did an amazing job. 

Definitely recommend them for your everyday alterations and more intricate requests!
Fantastic space, laid back attitude and no name is amazing. I bought 6 shoes of espresso and left the place to partake on one of the most amazing adventures.. Ever :)

This is a smaller cemetary with no trees or grassy areas, but it's the oldest cemetary in New Orleans and chock full of amazing tombs.  Interesting folks aside from the best known are Homer Plessy, the Civil Rights icon, Paul Morphy of chess fame, Bernard de Marigny who we can thank for craps & Lafitte pirate Barthelemy Lafon!

Nightmare.  Run, done walk from this place.  After 35 minutes, I got my food and the dishes from previous customer still weren't cleared.  Eggs were gross and cold.
There really should be a zero stars option

HORRIBLE. Contracted thru Home Depot. Wrong measurements, sinks mounted wrong, lied to me, and tried to cheat me. Took THREE months to do a job I was told would take 2 days tops. Finally filed a complaint with BBB, Licensing Board and disputed CC charges. THEN they did what needed to be done. THEN I got district managers to coordinate the job. The US Granite office staff is incompetent. Not only do they not know how to manage a calendar but the never return phone calls. Happy with it now, but I'll never use them again.

We hadn't planned on eating here on vacation, but we are so glad we did because the food is delicious.  The wait staff isn't very friendly (except for one male server), but don't let that vibe throw you off. 

Order the banana pudding French toast!!! It was delicious. I can't even describe how tasty it is...
We ordered beer and appetizers (except for the French toast) and the bill was around $100 with the tip, so it is on the pricier side, but the food is fresh and good.   It wasn't crowded (shocker), they have a decent bar, and the food is great.  Visit if you have a chance.  It was our favorite place on vacation!

Man I love this place. I've been there twice now and each time was phenomenal. Tonight I went with some friends and I'm newly dairy and egg free due to an allergy - I hate asking for accommodations because I try not to be difficult... but our server was amazing and without any issue ensured everything I got was dairy and egg free. To make the night even better she gave me a peach sorbet for dessert so I wouldn't feel left out since my friends ordered dessert. So nice! The food here is delicious and the portion sizes are more than reasonable. Love it!
I was born and raised in Maryland. The crab was like a taste from the past! Hard to find good crab outside of Maryland but Blake did the job!!

I order a BBQ pulled pork sandwich and French onion soup the pork was dry and not much barbecue sauce the soup was microwaved so the cheese would melt and the cheese was rubber 
For the first time at this establishment ever I will not be going back there , 
Also the waitress was not very attentive she and her co workers and manager was their discussing restaurant scheduled and operations in front of customers not very professional... In my opinion probably why they have not had a review since 2015

Three words...$2 Taco Tuesdays!!!! My favorite is the oyster taco.  They have a good happy hour with beer, margaritas, a signature cocktail, and more for $5 and under.  Love the ambiance and drinking out of mason jars.  Fun place with good food.

I don't know why this place is so busy. We thought both our meals were gross! Biscuits were way over done. Gravy had no flavor. The sausage tasted horrible and was burnt. The crab cakes I didn't taste but they looked gross and 3/4 the way thru he found a dead nat in it.

Joyce was so communicative and helpful when there was a glitch with our ride traveling back to the city from a tour about 35 minutes away. She was in contact with my group and the driver and coordinated everything. The driver also contacted me when he was close to our location. When it ultimately did not work out, she refunded the money back to my card. I would recommend Joyce T. Marsalis and Let's Just Ride for your transportation needs.

The menu may not be as extensive as some Chinese places in town, but everything we've tried has been great. Everything is freshly prepared and hot when it comes out. The sauces are all tasty and just the right consistency--not too much corn starch. The service has been great--the staff is friendly and attentive without being annoying. We got Christmas dinner to go because hubby was in the hospital and they gave us a package of almond cookies. How many places do things like that?

Fast casual Korean restaurant with some hits and misses. Stick with the more mainstream dishes -- really impressed with their hot stone bibimbap, and their Katsu was good too. Skip the soondubu (soft tofu soup). 

The first time I went here, I was super disappointed in the soft tofu stew I ordered.  The broth tasted watery and not very authentic. Maybe this was partially my fault for ignoring the cashier recommendations (bibimbap or Korean fried chicken). 

The second time I came here I ordered the make-your-own bibimbap (with a stone pot) and it totally redeemed rice & mix!! You can pick 5 veggies, 1 protein, and a mild/med/spicy gochujang sauce. This will set you back around $12, which is reasonable imo. The best part of this was how long the bowl stayed hot!! Literally 30 minutes later, the rice was still crackling and I was able to get a good sear on my rice and mushrooms. Very impressed. 

Additional notes:
- Not a traditional place, as there is no banchan here :(
- most bibimbaps come with a raw egg, but here that's an add on charge of $1
- the spicy gochujang is the most authentic--the mild isn't as good

To be honest, this place does not deserve any of theose 4-5 stars...... come on it's a place to serve food n all you can see around you is dust n dirt while waiting for the food..... 
The place needs a good thorough clean -up and some good light before any food is served.
Now coming to the important aspect - Taste n Quality of their food..... its a definitely a thumbs down.
I have been going to PENANG for over 10 years n till date their taste n quality remains as it was all those years back.
It is not even worth writing about every dish, since none of the 3 dishes me n my wife ordered were impressive. We ordered the roti canai which was so-so. This was followed by the chicken satay which is a NO-NO!!. If you are fan of the thai chicken satay, please don't even bother ordering this here, cause it is very BAD. Then last but not the least we ordered the thai basil noodles n once again were left disappointed. We read so much about this place (including reviews on yelp), that every time we went to Penang, we thought of taking our chance at banana leaf the next time we ventured for Malaysian cuisine. Now we are glad that we took our chance so late n this is definitely the end of it.  So here it is concluding my review with just these last words...... Banana leaf is not even worth taking that one chance onwhen you can truly experience great Malaysian food at PENANG which serves amazing flavors n a super ambience!!  Aslo want to add that Penang is truly accommodating for vegetarians too.

Just opened last week. I had Jamaican jerk wings that were unbelievably good...tender and sweet and spicy all at the same time. 5 full wings connected to the leg for $12....actually a lot of food.

The fries are the best I have had in twenty years. Reminiscent of Thrashers from OC, MD. Outstanding with malt vinegar and a deal at two sizes ($3.50 or $6).

Bassett's ice cream !!

Very helpful wait staff
Cheapest prices in town and great selection! If you're looking for anything in particular let them know and they'll be able to track it down for you!

Great NOLA snack food!  Similar to Cheetos, but denser and rocking with more robust flavors.  My favorite is the original, but green onion is a close second.   I cannot keep these around the house, or I will binge-eat them compulsively in one sitting.  And yet when I'm not here, I will sometimes beg friends or family to mail them to me (shameless!)  

Free shipping across the U.S. for those who can't make it down here enough to satisfy their CheeWee cravings.  (http://www.elmerscheewees.com/default.asp)

(I haven't tried the caramel corn because I'm not a sweet person, but in my mind, Elmer's Fine Foods can do no wrong.)

Couldn't be more happy with my first time experience with Public Storage, and for that matter first time using any type of storage unit.

Brandee took me under her wing and made sure I had the unit that would fit my needs. She reviewed the contract with me and did a last minute cleaning of the unit for me before I started moving my stuff in.  

My Unit is a 10x10 and is at least 10 feet high, I choose an outdoor unit so I could easily just drive up and unload once. 

I reserved my unit online, 1st month was only $1, plus a one time admin fee of $24, and I need to buy a lock for $19, pretty reasonable I thought. Total was a bit more with taxes and such.

I would defiantly recommend them.

Food was great. Service was kind, but slow. Not sure if they were under staffed or not enough cooks, but it took right at 20 minutes to get our appetizer and then another 30 for entrees. I'd try it again, maybe on a Tuesday or Wednesday evening.
Amazing burger. Fish tacos were great, made with fresh catch of the day. Today was swordfish. Nice small area and grey place to eat if visiting the Salvador Dali museum.

I ordered 2 plates of food with a dessert and my total was over $49. Big Mama's is overpriced. This wouldn't be a problem if the taste out weighed the price. Unfortunately that didn't happen the chitterlings were very greasy and chopped up very small. They're also supposed to be kind of meaty which is a sign of them being well done. But these chitterlings were still somewhat soft. The spaghetti was cold and I was told it couldn't be heated because of the cold slaw ( why wasn't it already warmed before adding it to the plate.) The fried chicken plate wasn't as bad. The fried chicken actually tasted good. However my pinto beans and collard greens tasted as if they were from a can! I won't be revisiting Big Mama's soul food again. The quality wasn't worth the price!!!

Now that is what I call authentic mexican food! I have been going to Los Arroyos since I first moved to Santa Barbara in 2008 and it has been consistently amazing. The food is always rich in flavor, the service is cordial and attentive and the margaritas are just perfect! 
I basically know their menu by heart by now so I must mention a few of my favorites:

1 Burrito Mojado -- (I could eat this every single day and never get tired of it)
2 Steak Tacos a Mano (Simple and tasty)
3 Ceviche (Perfect for a warm summer day. Pair it with a Dueno Margarita)
4 Chile Relleno or even better, Chile Relleno Burrito
5 Maria's Enchiladas ( The best enchiladas I have ever tried!)

I also must mention that their prices are really good, specially around the Cito area.
Love this place. Very good food. Never had anything that wasn't good. They get very busy so you may want to call ahead. Highly recommend.

This was my first CrossFit gym, and I have to say it was amazing.  The gym itself is in great shape in this large vaulted warehouse, with plenty of space for everyone to safely workout (not like I have seen at other gyms).  Jeff is a great coach, and I really appreciate the attention to detail they give all of their athletes on form, and being safe.  And for someone like me who was completely new to everything I really appreciated the time the coaches took to make sure you were doing things correctly .They also offer other programs such as Olympic Lifting, and more bootcamp style workouts if you don't want to go solely into CrossFit.

Overall I really enjoyed my time at Fearless and if I still lived in Philly I would still be going there.  If you are in Philadelphia and looking for a new gym, you should definitely give Fearless a try!

My boyfriend brought me to Viva for Valentine's Day and we had the best time! We were able to sit outside in the patio that was heated up and look at the beautiful lights and fountain. The service was very friendly and attentive. Food and drinks were DELICIOUS!!

Very good BBQ ribs! The sauce has a nice flavor, and the meat is tender. Tailgate Barbecue is a great local place to come for some quick take-out if you want a good and filling meal. The collard greens and salad are nice sides to go with the ribs. The chicken wings are also tasty.

The restaurant staff is friendly and accommodating. Much of their food is gluten free, and the staff is happy to discuss ingredients for customers like me, who have food allergies. 

All in all, a good addition to Glenside!

Came to New Orleans to visit and eat as much sea food as possible, so I went to Luke...randomly picked the place..didn't know what to eat but stuffed oysters sounded good so here I was 1/2 dozen stuffed oysters..shortly after I figured how to eat them (with the spoon to get all of it, as the manager said) there were none left!!! So good

Came here for dinner yesterday,  and the wait was about 45-60mins. Still a pretty long wait for a weekday, but I'm sure much better compared to the weekend crowd.  Regardless, the wait was worth it! We had the Black Roasted Garlic, and it was amazing! The broth was deep and flavorful, the noodles were thin and plentiful, and the pork was tender.  Only thing I didn't care for was the community tables. Other than that, I am so glad Tucson finally has its own dedicated Ramen Spot... about time!

So wife and I hit up this joint right after the new owners took over and they bent over backwards to see that we were happy with the food. So basically, there are my thoughts:

1.  They do RC Cola products, which is AWESOME!
2. Their gyro is strong, and their crinkle-cut fries hit the spot.
3. I tried the Sonoran Dog, and it was overcooked. I was sad kitty, but understand that mistakes happen.

To me, this is the type of place that will be hit or miss because it's still getting its feet underneath it, and yes, good help is hard to find.  They are open to suggetions, and are looking to make a name in the local east side community.  I wish them the best and plan on returning soon to try something new.

I purchased a sofa from Ashley in store in June. I paid in full as required and was told by the sales person I'd get a delivery date texted. It's 3 weeks later, and all I've received is a text to say I have no delivery date. I called the company and was routed to a call center who said they still didn't have a delivery date but were trying to get one. While on hold, I was listening to their marketing boast that they design and make their own furniture, have their own distribution centers and handle their own delivery. So the failure to arrange a delivery for a fully purchased product is squarely on the shoulders of Ashley. I was then told I have to go to the store or try to get through to them to cancel the order. After 14 calls to the local store, I was able to cancel the order and pay a 10% penalty! I just paid $100 for this store who can't deliver what I purchased! I'd rather give them that than $1000. I will never shop there again. I was told this is a problem in the furniture industry right now. While I understand there's a pandemic, that doesn't explain why this company who has total control over the sourcing, supply, and distribution of their stock cannot communicate a delivery date. I have purchased furniture from other retailers over the past two months, and while delivery has taken them longer (due to the pandemic), they've been able to deliver! And communicate! Ashley should be ashamed. And they should wave their cancellation fee. If they had done that, I might consider buying from them again. Now? No way.

I love Jules pizza!! I had it first when they opened in Doylestown, PA and I have loved it ever since. The cherry Hill location keeps up with the fresh ingredients and pleasant workers. Today I had a "slice" of their Mexican pizza...oh my goodness it was ssoo delicious. The chipotle sauce drizzled on it had just the right amount of kick without leaving my mouth on fire. The fresh corn, tomatoes, and cilantro were such a great match with the black beans. Everything was amazing.

I placed an interest in a trailer they had on their website. A salesman contacted me via email. We talked back and forth and we finally went in. We were looking at 2 specific trailers when we arrived and the salesman Jonny was there and ready. He took us to see what we requested but I guess he had a feeling we weren't satisfied. He suggested seeing another trailer and told us it was above our price range. We looked and fell in love! It hit all our needs and the price wasn't that far from our budget after sale. It was easy, no pressure and enjoyable to work with HitchRv and Jonny! They're even helping us with our hitch set up!! Financial guy Mike was also awesome bc he was able to get our rate lower then what we were quoted!! Win-win!!!

NTB is so amazing. My dog absolutely love it there. I don't have anything to complain about. Devin and his staff are the best. They help to create such a positive and fun environment. My dog has been there for 6 months and he is so happy every single time.
Update to the update. Says I'll get a response from management and over 15 days later I've not gotten a reply to my initial email

They do a good job but 3rd time making an appointment and 3rd time I had to wait.  Not sure why they take appointments.  2nd time I said something to the gentleman and he assured me next time I would be taken at the appointment time.  Nope.  Actually this time I was taken 40 minutes later.  I received no apology not even any acknowledgement that they were late.  If I was told it would be 40 minutes, I would have gone somewhere else.  If you have all day to sit in a nail salon, go for it.  If not, there are plenty of other nail salons that do just as good of a job.
All the beer tasted bad- the keg lines were old/bad. Gave back 2 beers, still charged us. Lame

Came for the mnm in out event. Arrive 5:30pm. Phone line busy. No orders at the door. Uber eats currently unavailable for location. 
Went up to the window. Was told to call after 6:30pm when calls die down. Todd was not nice about it either. We left to find food elsewhere.

Wasn't aware the restaurant changed hands 2 years ago.  Picked up chicken paprikash and stuffed cabbage.  While the cabbage was great, very disappointed w the chicken dish.  I've had this before in numerous restaurants and it usually comes in a chicken broth w sour cream, very juicy.  This was almost like a chicken in a gravy, very dry, not juicy at all.  Just my preference, but the previous owner had it down, very authentic.
Very clean place, peaceful and inviting environment. The people were nice abs they did a great job.

Alright yes their Banana French Toast has been very consistent and great. I used to love their Lobster Benedict but that has not been consistent. And you know what else? Their service! 

Probably only been here four times and the first time was the main reason why I kept returning. Any time after that it was not great at all. the wait time seemed to increase, my order seem to just be wrong, and food just went downhill.

Very disappointed..I don't think I will come back ever..

I would have to agree with most of the reviews on here about this place. I've only gotten take-out from here once, but it was well worth it!

The only concern that I had with the tacos was that they put a bit too much cheese on them, other than that they were great.

Had the steak tacos and I believe El Pastor pork tacos with pineapple.
Also ordered a side of beans and rice.  all good and would suggest to anyone in the S. Philly area to check this place out.

I'm from outside New Orleans, but recently moved to Oakland, CA. I frequently Hey! On a monthly basis, as I love specialty coffee and this shop is very consistent and in a few great locations in the city.

My friend Devin, who is a local roaster in Hammond, LA and I had been talking about Yemeni coffee and trying to get our hands on some. For those unfamiliar, Yemen was one do the first places coffee was grown and cultivated. It's also a hard region to export from, modern-day. I was very pleasantly surprised when this showed up at my door, sent from Devin!

I brewed a cup immediately using my Hario V60, and it was fresh and bright. The jasmine came out for me in the tasting notes, giving it a light and almost tea-like body. 

I've always loved this space to frequent, but this was an extra special surprise!

Terrible experience, time after time again! I gave this place quite a few tries but it only led to greater disappointments. I don't usually like to leave bad reviews, but I felt that it was important to make a mention of my experience for those customers who know they care about the nail service they receive. The techs are very rude, rough and sloppy in their work- they just want to get you in and out of there as soon as possible as they want greater turn-over of customers thus more money. They charge too high of price is comparison to the current average nail salon rates. Oh, also, if you don't leave a good tip they will curse you out on your way out the door in a language they think you don't understand. For myself, I prefer to stay away from toxic people and places and this review was long postponed, but here it finally is and is well deserved.

Stumbled on this place looking for a quick bite to eat. Our server was great! Very nice and attentive, making sure he had our order correct before leaving the table. When we mentioned we were in a bit of rush, he was very helpful in making sure we were quickly taken care of. We got the $5 burger special and they were amazing. Perfectly juicy with all the right toppings. The only thing that I can say needed improvement was the beer list. The only list was on a small chalkboard on one wall by the door. The atmosphere was homey and friendly and the food was just right. I will definitely return here!

Given the current times, I have only ordered takeout from this location and haven't had the opportunity to dine in and really enjoy the space! Thst being said, this particular location is smaller than the one downtown and they also have less space to dine in, however, that could also be a result of Covid related restrictions. 

Service was prompt and staff was patient when waiting for me to decide which items to order. I settled on the Iced Houjicha latte and the Yuzu Mousse cake. 

The Houjicha latte looks a bit like dirt and not super appetizing, but I promise it is delicious. It has a super nutty, roasted flavour and perfect iced or hot. The Mousse cake was like most Japanese desserts, light and flavours, subtle. I would definitely order the yuzu mousse cake again!

Worst dealership ever. The only good thing is there service department. There prices are higher then any other Kia dealer and Joe the manager is HORRIBLE and yells at customers and reneges on promises.

We enjoyed both a great breakfast and a great lunch here recently. Our servers were friendly, sweet and on their A-game. The very small kitchen has a little trouble keeping up with the demand of the closely-packed tables. Highest praise for the fried green tomatoes and the avocado bowl. The Caesar salad had freshly grilled chicken and thick shavings of parmesan. The oyster po boy was full of outstanding oysters and served on really good bread. There were a couple of disappointments: the coffee tasted as if it had been stewing too long and the pancakes weren't warm when they hit the table, but they were still tasty. Will definitely return.
Good prices and good pizza. You have a wide variety of toppings you can add before receiving an additional charge. Always fast and clean.

Great service and amazing tacos and soup.   I had the sausage lentil soup and enjoyed every spoonful.

Highly recommend their happy hour between 4-6pm weekdays.

I'll be back!!!

We called Prestige Towing after waiting for AAA for 45 minutes and then being told it would be another hour!  I called AAA and canceled and had Prestige Towing pick up our vehicle.  They were at our truck in 20 minutes.  The young man was professional, brave (465 on Memorial Day during rush hour with semi trucks coming within inches of him) and he knew what he was doing.  They towed our 1986 Chevy 4 WD with a 6" lift  to the repair shop and then sent us pictures after they arrived.

Thank you so much for your help today, we appreciate it!!
The drinks are great along with the service however the past few times I've tried to come here they've been closed. They change they're hours every other day which is a inconvenience.

My husband and I had the pleasure of trying this place several weeks back at the end of May on our short honeymoon in Florida. We were both born and raised in Hawaii and lived almost our whole lives there, so we've been really missing local food from home now that we've transplanted to Georgia. Sure, we can make a lot of the dishes back home, but it's different not being able to just pull up to a spot to get the comfort food we're used to when we don't want to cook. There were like two places in the Atlanta area that did Hawaiian-Asian style plate lunches like this and now only one of those is still open near us, so it was awesome to find this place while traveling. 

There's a small parking lot to the side and around the little building, with a seemingly ample amount of stalls as it was dead when we went. There's a picnic table behind the store, but we decided to eat in, since we were the only ones ordering at the time. The guys were super nice at the counter when we ordered and brought our food to the table for us when ready. We got the canned Liliko'i juice, spam musubis, and two Big Kahuna plates which consisted of shoyu chicken, kalua pig, teriyaki beef and white rice with pineapple coleslaw on the side. Everything was awesome - big portions and authentic flavors! I know some people will argue that kalua pig is not authentic unless cooked in an imu, but you do what you gotta do here in the mainland USA with limited resources. Now if there was an easy way to access Hawaii brands of Portuguese sausage, poi, and lau lau (with the true taro leaves), then we'd be all set. 

All in all, we really enjoyed the food and atmosphere and are looking forward to coming back next time we're in Florida again. The food paired with a day at beautiful Siesta Key made this first time trip to Florida together a memorable one that evoked sweet nostalgia from home. If you've never had a local plate lunch from Hawaii, stop in here if you're in the area. I'm sure there's something here for everyone, and if not, at least you tried something new!

Holy Smokers... I have to take a minute to pause to digest how amazing this food is tasting in my mouth right now!! Literally past by here enroute to Da Capo and.. wow... we have found a gem.  If you want an amazing Japanese experience more than just sushi and ramen, definitely check this place out.

This place is great! Was down there the other weekend after a 20 year hiatus (residing in Phoenix currently) and it still had the same feeling! Used to perform in the  Rocky Horror Picture Show when I was younger and brought back some nice memories. Not the most comfortable theater to sit in, but still one of the most fun to visit! Highly recommended!

Yes, yes and yes. Everything here was amazing: Dan Dan Noodles, Garlic Chicken and Salt and Pepper Shrimp. Cannot wait to go back. Service was very good as well. Spicy, but really not too spicy and you can definitely have them adjust the spiciness depending on your preference. I would recommend sharing as there are so many good things to try. Enjoy!

This creepy looking guy who works there thinks it's ok to slam a vacuum hose into your car as he is trying to straighten it out. I was giving him the stink eye as a result and all he did was smile at me sheepishly, as if I was staring at him in admiration. He then just kept staring back at me as I was leaving. The car wash itself is great, but that ex-con looking man shouldn't be allowed near people's cars!

I called first thing Monday morning as my dads refrigerator had stopped working. The lady that answered the phone was very pleasant. I asked if I could get an afternoon appointment and she got me set up for a repair after 12:00pm. Walter called a short time after 12:00pm and said he would be there in 10 minutes. He arrived and introduced himself and got right to work. He explained what he was doing, what was wrong and figured out the problem right away. He even had the part in his van. He got it up in running in no time. Thank you so much Walter for fixing my dads refrigerator.
GREAT brunch!!!  Excellent quality, good variety and friendly service.

This place is so dirty. They had premade chicken in a bucket where they keep their drinks and then threw into deep fryer! Woman was handling food and money. This place needs a surprise health inspection! Never again

We walked over here from midtown during a drizzly Saturday morning. I wouldn't advise the trip from Charlotte Avenue, as the sidewalks are quite disjointed, and some intersections don't have crosswalk lights. The farmers' market itself, fortunately, is sheltered by massive, sturdy rooves, so (rain or shine), patrons can enjoy the plentiful bounty offered by vendors. We salivated by the homemade pies available at every corner, and indulged in a bit of Jeni's ice cream as well as lunch in the restaurant area. I headed over to the Sloco organic sandwich section while my partner lined up for a breakfast crepe. Both of us waited only a little while for satisfying and rich lunch time deliciousness. I got a chicken pesto sandwich with creamy goat cheese; the chicken was a bit dry, but the creamy goat cheese and thick bread definitely made up for it. 

The produce offered seemed more affordable than other farmers' markets I've frequented, and they garnered decently large crowds at almost every stand. While you may not find in-store prices, the freshness and hospitality you'll experience will be unbeatable.

I would recommend coming on a sunnier day, as we went on quite a grey and nippy morning.

Highly recommended!  Lockmobile provided excellent service and did it very quickly.  I called and they showed up in less than an hour on a weekend, and it wasn't even an emergency.  Bill had the expertise and skill to change a lot of locks for me in a short amount of time.

Such a great way to start our last day in the area...thank you Mike for all of your help and information in advance and the day of our rental. I would highly recommend Woody's Watersports and will be back again!

My car needed a wash and vacuum badly. Saw this car wash while I was driving by and pulled in. I was very impressed with there system of operation and the keen sense to detail. People cleaning and the man behind the desk were kind and respectful of my property. My car looked great. I would definitely use them again and again.
The food here is consistently good. Delivery is fast and the food always arrives piping hot. Employees are very pleasant, I think it's the best in the Drexel Hill area.

If you're looking for cannolis, this is the place to go.  Always fresh and delicious.  You can get mascarpone or ricotta filling.  Both are fantastic! Like other yelpers mentioned, the ladies behind the counters aren't the friendliest. So don't be offended if your goods are not served with a smile.

I went here for the first time a few days ago and really enjoyed it! I'm a vegan and they completely catered to my food needs, creating  a custom dish for me at my request.

The menu is extensive. They have seasonal specials, pastas, salads, meat entrees, and seafood dishes. The prices are extremely reasonable for such tasty food and portions. The dishes were very large and the waitress even gave us a portion to take home when our dishes weren't listed under the section of the menu with that offer! She was super friendly and helpful. 

I got an Italian salad for start and it was perfectly dressed and very tasty; as a vegan, I eat a ton of salad, and this one was definitely up to par. The rolls they served complimentary before ordering were warm and fluffy, with quality olive oil to dip. I had the kitchen create me a dish with wheat pasta, veggies (onions, zucchini, peppers, etc), and marinara. Sooo tasty! Like mom's homemade Sunday gravy. My brother and other companions all praised their dishes as well - lasagna, chicken parm, and fettuccine Alfredo; check out my photos for them!

There was no vegan dessert option, sadly, as pretty much all restaurants neglect to put on the menu. The people I was with for creme brûlée, apple crostini, lemon cookies, and a pound cake slice with caramelized bananas, also in my photos. All smelled heavenly! 

To drink, we split a small pitcher of the seasonal sangria ($26/pitcher): moscato, vodka, strawberry, lemon, cantaloupe, and pineapples. I swear, this was the best cocktail or sangria or wine anything in my entire life! Soooo yummy! Definitely recommend!

The atmosphere on the Saturday evening before Mother's Day was very hectic, but the table was clean and service attentive for the most part.

The only negative was that they gave us a 1.5 hour wait time, then soon they changed it to 2 hours. The majority of our party went to the mall to wait, and 15 minutes later they called to say the table was ready! Not everyone was there yet, so they wouldn't seat anyone and said we only had ten minutes to all be there. Kind of absurd since they gave a 2 hour wait time and called after only 15 minutes... Hosts definitely need to work on their estimation skills!

Overall, I will definitely return and look forward to doing so! I highly recommend if you love salad, pasta, and alcohol as much as I do!

Want to preface this by saying the food was amazing, the place was nice, very cute and in a great location near Jackson Square. However, the service was horrendous. We called at 10 am to put our names on the list and were told we would be seated at 11. We had a party of 7 so we drove in two cars. The car that got there first was told that they would not put our names on the list until our whole party was there, and that there were fifteen people ahead of us and now we would have to wait two more hours. We understood that it was a Sunday morning in a busy location so we decided to walk around and wait. When we came back after receiving a text from the restaurant that our table was ready, we were told we still had to wait. The seventh member of the party was parking the car in a spot directly in front of French Toast while the rest of us waited out front. Again, we were told by the host that they wouldn't seat us until she was there and the host also yelled at us for standing in front of the restaurant despite not letting us inside while we waited for out table. Once we finally got our table, we were treated extremely rudely by our waitress Allie who unnecessarily snapped at several members of our group. We are not a difficult group of people by any means so we were shocked that our waitress was being so snippy. She yelled at us for not ordering in the correct order, at one of our friends for being on her phone, and for another friend for asking to use Apple Pay. Allie also neglected to check on us the entire time we were eating and we had to essentially beg her to bring her our checks, which we waited nearly 15 minutes on. When our checks came, we had been overcharged for an item and instead of voiding it, three dollars were thrown at us as compensation. We were really excited about this place based on the rave reviews it has but were so disappointed by the lack of NOLA hospitality from the French Toast employees. This was a sour ending to our otherwise lovely visit. I would urge others to check out another local place that they would be treated kinder at.

My friends and I decided to come to Tampa for a vacation but I didn't have time to do my nails. So, I decided to do a quick stop here at Joy's nail & spa to start my vacation looking on point. Angela attended me and I was BLOWN AWAY. I'm usually a picky person with how my nails turn out, always telling my tech to fix certain things but not with Angela. She's a perfectionist, patient, and extremely sweet. I'm contemplating driving her once a month from Orlando! I'm content and grateful I stopped by. Ask for
Angela!!

This place is amazing!! Everyone makes you feel so at home and the customer service is absolutely wonderful!! It feels like you're at a family reunion every time I come here!! Hands down amazing food and atmosphere!! The Palace Grill is a must in Santa Barbara!! Brittany is such a lovely soul! Super sweet and excellent server!! If I could give a 10 star review I would!!
great food....great prices....huge quantity of food...very friendly staff....great diner environment.  I'll be back...

When I checked in, I couldn't believe how personable the staff members were. I felt welcomed immediately. On top of that, check in was a breeze and took no time at all. 

I was lucky enough to get upgraded to a suite, and it was fantastic. It felt more like an apartment than a hotel room, which I loved. It was quiet since road noise was minimal. 

The property looks well-maintained, and I didn't see any bugs (rare for Florida). All of my towels and bedsheets were clean, so no complaints there. 

If you're in the area, definitely consider staying here!
Mackenzie our server gave us excellent recommendations.  The food was superb and the company even better! Top of the line live music enjoyed on the patio in our amazing Florida weather!

I've had very long hair for years and decided it was time to get rid of it. I got a Groupon for Shine and made an appointment. The day I was there, Laura was the only one there, everyone else was at a convention in San Francisco, so I can't speak for the ventilation as another reviewer mentioned. The salon space is small, but I didn't find it cramped. The decor is contemporary and natural. The product line is wonderful and the staff is knowledgeable about them.  

The last two times I had my hair done in an "upscale" salon were both disappointing. One time, the stylist talked the whole time about herself and did only a basic trim on my long hair and charged me $39. The second time, the stylist didn't say anything and did only what I told her to do. I got better service at the Supercuts for $20! 

When I sat down with Laura, she took the time to look at the pictures I brought, look at me and my hair and actually make suggestions about what would look good. I had brought a couple friends with me and she very graciously let them hang out and take pictures. Laura cut almost a foot off my hair and the salon arranged to donate the hair for me. The haircut was exactly what I wanted, even though I didn't know exactly what I wanted! It looks great on me and works great with my very curly hair. Not everyone does well with curly hair, but Laura took the curl into account when cutting and kept scrunching it as she cut to see where it would curl up. She recommended product that worked with my new style. I am thrilled with the results and will definitely be back!

This place is a dump. The bar is not actually that bad. Plenty of room. The bartenders ruin the place. They are rude and miserable. The prices seemed to change by the round. I guess they would rather rip you off than actually do their job with a pleasant attitude and earn good tips. Never again

So we have eaten at this china wok a hand full of times, and got nothing but fantastic food and quick deliveries. My wife is a vegan and we order the mei fun noodles only veggies no eggs, and the general tso's bean curd. I must say they make the best bean curd I've ever had. We picked up an order from there the other day, got home and realized that the mei fun had meat, just a mistake on the packing end of things. We called the restaurant and let them know what happened, and they had the veggie mei fun noodles delivered to our house within 20 minutes. If you ask me that is great customer service. Being a chef de cuisine I appreciate the way they handled things no questions asked, just an apology and question of what they can do to make things right. Best Chinese food in the largo area that we have found so far.

This was such a fun adventure, and a definite highlight of our vacation. Captain Dylan was great, we loved him! Knowledgeable, entertaining, and his personality really shined. Also, I got to pet a baby gator and that's a dream come true. We came in last week of March, which gave great weather and a number of wildlife sightings: various birds, gators, turtles.

I had an interesting experience at this place...

My boyfriend and I had been out drinking and were walking down Bourbon Street on the way back to our hotel. We were both pretty inebriated and having a great time. We pass by the Old Opera House (by the way, don't let the name fool you, this place is just another dumpy Bourbon street bar populated by drunk frat boys), and the lovely hostess in front of the bar starts talking to us. She calls us a cute couple, chats with us for a little while, and ends up offering us shots out of test tubes (don't ask). We're not the kind to refuse a free drink, so my boyfriend and I indulge in "a few" shots (crappy booze, by the way). Ten minutes of friendly conversation and a few shots later, our lovely hostess becomes serious, and flatly tells us that we owe her $48. As we realize, we are also surrounded at this point by two big bouncers. 

WTF? She offered us the shots, never said they were for sale, never told us a price or gave us any indication that we'd get charged for them. By that time, she wasn't the friendly person who'd lured us in anymore... We tried to argue with her and her bouncer friends, who decided simply to threaten to call the police: "You pay or go to jail". Are you effin' kidding me? Pay or go to jail, for drinks that we never ordered?

We ended up going in the back, talking to the manager (who blended right in in the crowd of dimwitted frat boys), and after a few minutes of argument ended up paying $24 for the shots of crappy booze that we never ordered but were simply put in our hands. 

Lesson learned: Bourbon street is a tourist trap. Don't count on the generosity of strangers there: people are after your money, and will take advantage of your drunkenness to squeeze it out of you. Just pathetic.

I'm a big proponent of supporting local businesses, and I've always enjoyed Brew-HaHa! since high school.

Step into the shop, and it's a genuine coffee shop and cafe, with fresh pastries and sandwiches waiting for you to purchase. The decor is very Euro with the small wooden tables and wall hangings. There are lots of drink options (coffee and non) on the chalkboards as well. I think it's brilliant that they name their sandwiches after local neighborhoods - brings the local feel right down to earth. I like getting the chicken salad sandwich and pairing it up with a nice iced chai.

Service is always friendly, but don't be in a mad rush to get out the door. 

Overall, it's always nice to slow down and enjoy some time at Brew-HaHa!

It was okay. I wanted to try the cannolis so I got 2 mini ones and a lemon bar. The lemon bar was good but I was disappointed with the cannolis. They had more spice in either the shell or filling than I think a cannoli should. Wasn't totally blown away.

I came here for a late lunch. This establishment is quite large especially their bar. I found the service good but a little slow for my liking. I ordered the burger and the bread pudding. While the burger was good, it was quite small. It came with sweet potatoe fries which were tasty. The real MVP was the chocolate bread pudding. It is made to order so make sure you place your order as soon as possible. It was delicious. It came in an ethereal mug that was very hot. I savored every bite even though I was running late for one of my conference sessions. So worth it! I hear great things about their brunch but I never made it back to try it out.
My mom and I traveled to India, and we loved the food.  This place is as authentic as it gets.  Highly recommended.  Enjoy!
Website advertises they're open until 1 am. I just tried hitting the place up after a show at the pageant down the street. The door was locked and chairs were stacked on the table at 10:30.
Food was good but portions were so tiny. Not from New Orleans I guess. 10 pieces of pasta for $19. They're new maybe they'll come around.

The only thing I knew about Nicaragua before was that the people there speak Spanish but, now I realized that their food is 'da bomb!' I am a frequent visitor here and maybe it's because of the latino/hispanic culture but, the workers here are crazy friendly. They run out of desserts fast here so the owner, Orlando, told me to call in ahead of time and he would save e some-now that's hospitality.

If it's your first time eating food from Nicaragua (which it probably is) then a safe recommendation would be ordering the Carne Asada dish. It's simple but, a common meal from Nicaragua that comes with a marinated steak and your choice of two sides.

Also, with each meal you'll receive a plate containing three condiments: jalapenos, a homemade chipotle sauce, and a green mixture called chimichurri. Don't get me wrong, the food is already good but, adding these tangy mixtures will take your meal to another level. I don't know what or how they're made but, they're amazing.

The only negative (and it's not really a negative) about this place is sometimes the wait after ordering can be a little longer than normal but, I'm sure it's because they cook each meal to order. So when your food arrives it's fresh and steaming hot.

I suggest you get out your comfort zone and give Nicaraguan food a try if you haven't already.

I have been going to this Spa regularly for about 2 years now. I normally schedule all of my waxing appointments with Karmjeet. She is great. Very professional and also very kind. We always have friendly conversations and she does a very thorough job. I always leave feeling satisfied with my results. Yesterday I booked a last minute appt with Nikki. She was very kind and professional as well. She also did a fabulous job. I love this place!! Wouldn't risk going anywhere else.

Amy is the best! I know she works long hours with many clients, yet she gives great attention to details and takes her time in doing a thorough job... And she is a just a pleasant person to be around.

I can't give this movie theatre a very bad review because it is by far not the worst theatre I have been too.  The service isn't bad here either.  The seats are a little older but I have noticed them getting newer seat in some of there theaters.  As for talking about the second concession stand I have noticed it being open most the time I have been there and haven't had a problem with topping for popcorn.  The sound quality of the theatre is great also it is very crisp and it depends on the movie the surround sound will shake your seat.  This spot like all other movie theaters is a middle/high school hang out spot so you should expect that.  I really haven't experienced any of what the previous reviews have said not saying that its not sometimes like what they are saying.  It does need a new face lift though the outside is very plane.  But overall it's not a bad theater.

UPDATE:.....
They just did a complete update to the interior of this theater.  The inside concession areas have been completely redone and they have the new coke machines with about every type of coke product there is.  From what I noticed they have replaced all there seats with new leather reclining seats.  This is definitely one of the best movie theaters I have ever been too.  They have also done an update of the outside of the theater repainted and put up a new sign it looks a lot better.  They have done alot of great improvements of this movie theater.

I love this place! I hate buying this kind of stuff online - I want to see it before I spend my money on it...every purchase is intimate and you can't do that online. I love that they give a military discount, and they are very helpful yet not pushy. It's clean, items are priced well, and well, it's a fun place. Wish I could work there!
Mood has moved to a new location, their new address is 423 W. Girard Ave.  This information was posted in their window prior to the move.

This is probably the best and most creative vegan  restaurant I've visited. I loved the use of color and how much preparation/skill went into the entrees I've had here. Some vegan restaurants will serve things I can make a home and this place definitely has entrees I would never be able to make it at home.

Love this branch. It is always clean and there is a hot beverage machine that makes yummy coffees, hot chocolates, and teas. The staff is always friendly and helpful. I love having a local credit union right down the street from my house. I wish they would update their website but otherwise this is a great financial institution.

My hubs is obsessed with buffet's, me not so much but I do love Chinese so we stopped into Lin's.  The place was popping on a Sunday lunch time so I assumed it had to be pretty good.

The place is huge, and the selection bountiful.  Besides the standard Chinese dishes, they had a salad bar, American options, Sushi and Mongolian stir fry.  

The food was pretty good.  I did find the Orange Chicken to be really tough, almost unchewable.  But when you have this many options you just move on to something different.
