Given the price, you really can't lose as I believe we paid roughly $12 a piece.  The only drawback for me was that I had a tough time getting my water refilled despite all the people that worked there walking around.  

A solid OK if you buffets are your jam.
This place is pretty good. The deep fried Oreos make it worth it. Would recommend getting a pretty stacked hot dog. The elote cups are also pretty good. All my friends love this place

It's not bad! My first poké experience in Phili and it was pretty good (taste-wise). Lots of options to pick from, location is easy to get to, not too expensive (you are getting sashimi). However, they were extremely inconsistent when I came here for brunch yesterday. They gave my sister only 3 pieces of salmon, gave her mango by accident and then only gave her the tiniest bit of masago (fish egg) when fixing the order, and completely missed her bf's shrimp tempura. I think they were training a new guy, so I'll let them off the hook. The cashier was nice though and the free Cafe Benne tumbler (purchases over $20) was a nice touch. Also, the free lime water is very nice and refreshing!
Favorite place to eat in town. Don't go on Wednesday nights, or you'll have a long wait (the wait is often very long, but the food is worth it). TST is an institution.

As an initial disclosure, this was the second in-ground, gunnite swimming pool project that we did with the Doylestown, PA office of Anthony Sylvan (AS). The two projects were separated by 10 years and the pools were installed at two different locations.

From the beginning of this second engagement, the team at Anthony Sylvan (AS), headed by Sean Donohue, made the design and construction of our 20' X 40' swimming pool stress free. Hours were spent exchanging computer generated designs, schematics and elevations and then physically laying the pool out (which posed difficulties owing to the terrain and nit-picking local zoning officials who seemed more intent on obstructing development in this rural area than aiding rate payers).  AS took the lead on the permitting process, shepherding the permits through bureaucratic malaise and nit-picking. Actual construction was done as and when promised by subcontractors who worked efficiently, cleaned up the job-site after themselves and did not interfere with other trades engaged in an on-going residential construction project. AS's subcontractors were closely supervised by AS Construction Manager, Harald Bottke. Harald, like Sean Donohue, was attentive to our needs, anticipated our questions and concerns and provided us with daily telephonic, photographic and email reports. The construction project was finished as promised and on-budget.

Every step of the way, the pool passed the inspections the first time.

This spring, AS returned to open the pool for the first time. John visited twice during this process, familiarizing us with the equipment.  John was a gentlemen, took his time and was patient with our ridiculous questions.

Our only criticism of AS is that its in-house on-line payment system (ISwim) is somewhat cumbersome. In fairness, though, the system tracks the budgeting and payments well.

We have now used AS twice and would not hesitate to use AS again.

Our normal sushi delivery spot wasn't open so we tried Koto on a whim, and our delivery experience was pretty great. We ordered the vegetable gyoza, which had a perfect chew and flavorful filling. For rolls, my husband had the spicy tuna and salmon avocado, while I had the spicy tuna and tuna avocado. We shared an angel roll, as well. Everything was packaged nicely and the prices were fair. I'd try them again!

We walked in and the young lady behind the counter looked at us and then looked away.  There was no greeting.  She then went into the back.  After a few minutes, we left. If this was an example of their Customer Service, there is absolutely no way I would attempt to try their food.  I would not recommend this restaurant.

Went tonight with the family for dinner. Our waitress Courtney was awesome!  Tonight we tried the chicken parm rollers, French fries with sweet & sassy sauce & BBQ sauce, firehouse burger, & chicken sandwich!  Everything was delicious!!!!

The ONLY REASON I GIVE 3 is because the hospitality is something to be desired. EVERY time my son and I come in to eat we wait for at least 10 minutes after we are seen by at least 3 employees. Then when we are READY to order our waitress leaves us and doesn't come back fpr another 5 minutes AFTER she asks us if we are ready to order, I just don't get it. Why would you ask me if we are ready to order and then say "ok, I'll be right back" and not come back for 5 more minutes? My son was offered a coloring pad that never came. The hospitality here is something to be desired. The food is what brings us back. That's it! This is not a place for hospitable service, more of here it is and push you out!

5/5 nothing really to say other than absolutely the best. 
I got the with less sugar and that was still a bit sweet. BUT the tea is great. One of the better milk teas I've had in awhile. 
Also the bobas - they are different! 
The taste and chewiness is definitely better than some places that use bought bobas. 

Interior is also very hip and cozy. 
Absolutely would recommend this place

We arrived 15 minutes before closing and worried they may not want to seat us for dinner that late. But they were friendly, welcoming, and did not make us feel hurried. Our waitress was pleasant, and gave us plenty of time to make our dinner selections. We don't have Cracker Barrel's near us, and had heard mixed reviews, so I wasn't sure what to expect. We were very satisfied with our meal and the portion sizes were generous but not outrageously huge. Despite the late hour, the food did not taste stale or overlooked. We'd come here again. (But hopefully earlier so I can shop in their amazing gift shop!!) 
The "fried apples" are a must!! Tasted like hot apple pie filling without the crust.

Pod dining !!! Delicious drinks, yummy food from Heartbreakers and a private pod to enjoy it all in! Great concept amid the pandemic, great service and all around cool experience! I tried the painkiller and the scorpion ..something(I forgot the name) but both were really good quality drinks. Food was excellent I tried the adobe wings and a thing of fries. Just a wonderful way to get out of the house and spend time with friends

So this is truly outrageous fun for all ages!!! My wife surprised me for my birthday and took me here - knows I am a kid at heart.  We are in our 50's and both walked away completely amazed - really had a great experience.  There is something for everybody - choose from immersion experiences, fun games, to intense space battles or zombie hunting.  The staff are great - very helpful and there for you throughout the experience for help or playing tips.  We had no idea what to expect, but never thought it would be at this level.  Already talking about next visit.  Give it a try, you won't regret it!

Not bad but wouldn't come back if there was a wait.
Came here on a Sunday morning and luckily only had to wait for about 10-15 min.
The menu selection was pretty good and we opted for the stuffed French toast and the turkey bacon and  spinach eggs Benedict. The French toast was huge and could easily be shared. It was pretty good but a bit sweet but I wasn't expecting anything less. The eggs Benedict was OK, it was a bit runny and the spinach was gritty but the turkey bacon was good and crispy. 
The coffee was Ok but not the worst I've had.

Where to start...from Miami and was doing a road trip and ONLY stopped in St. Louis to go try out Salt + Smoke. Thank goodness for that decision because it was sooooo worth it. Went on a Tuesday evening and wasn't really expecting a wait time but there was. Was a little disappointed at first because they were out of brisket, pork, and chicken. The solution was the burnt end and it was mouth watering! Ordered that with Mac & cheese (probably best I've ever tried) along with baked beans. Again, a little upsetting they were out of the main stuff but i can only imagine it was just as good! Really wish they had a spot in south Florida  oh, and staff was super friendly and food comes out ridiculously fast (literally within 5 minutes or so of sitting).
Best place for breakfast. I did the Stanley Classic and it was amazing. Also, try the Bloody Mary it's to die for.

Best Hot Chocolate Ever!   The food is really good too, but it's not what brings me back.   Honestly, most of the time I go when I'm in the area and have eaten somewhere else already, and really just want some good hot chocolate.  If you do eat a meal here you won't be disappointed.  I've had the pizza and a few of there sandwiches and I've always liked them, though nutritionally whatever I get can't make up for the massive amounts of chocolate I get from my usual two hot chocolates and a dessert.

Great authentic Jamaican cuisine. Always fresh and delicious! Great menu and good inventory. 
Far superior in quality over many similar establishments.  
Stop by or call your order for pick-up.

Worst experience and worst food. The management is rude as hell. We asked for a replacement as food was not cooked properly and they started arguing why we did not like it and behaved very rudely with us. I will give a negative rating if there's an option. No one deserves a treatment like this especially for the money we pay.

I live in South Philly and I much prefer to walk to this location rather than drive to Home Depot. They have the basics for standard home repair and projects. The employees are very helpful and prompt. I highly recommend 1540. They even copy keys and sell bags of top soil!

If you are looking for boujee Tex Mex, this is for you! Had lunch with family and we ordered the romaine salad, guacamole, queso, and fajitas (to share). Not sure how to describe this place other than the fact that it's Mexican, but not? Maybe I should have adjusted my expectations, however, the food flavor came across as "basic Mexican." Service was also lacking, server wasn't really attentive and there weren't that many tables... so not sure what was happening there. Overall, I'd probably go back for drinks and not food.

The best donuts, hands down! Everything is absolutely delicious... the apple fritters are perfection and the ham & cheese croissants (if you can snag one) are melt in your mouth amazing. I am so glad it's not on my way to work, or I would be there every day.

Very nice service, the owner is quite nice and attentive.

I can only eat small portions so I just tried the appies the first time which were the Roti bread and spring rolls.  Both were very tasty, somewhat greasy, but the sauces were delicious for dips.

This place is all vegetarian which is perfect for those that don't eat meat.  And they sell many of their dishes in a couple coolers so that you can prepare them at home which is a great idea.

They also have a great selection of blooming teas.  I had the Japanese rice green tea and it was quite good, went well with the food.

The appies filled me up quite a bit almost to the point I had to get them to go, but forced myself to eat them because they were so good.

I don't think I would eat here every day because some of their dishes are quite pricey, but also many things are deep fried which is a no-no for me 99% of the time.

But for an occasional treat, this place is very cute, small and cozy.
New Brewery in town. Open for 3 weeks. They do a good job on all beers and have 5 to 8 beers on tap. Great addition to the neighborhood. It's turning into a mini brewery hood. Love it.

Worst experience in a hotel ever. We came here for the rib cook off during labor day weekend. The parking lot was full ( no problem ), we got an old room that smells like smoke on a non smoking floor ( no problem. Went to eat at Mels diner for dinner and the waitress who was in such a rush that she knocked over my glass of water that she just served me all over me. She was not very apologetic and didnt help clean up the mess, i thought i was in the twilight zone. It gets worse! Got up to my room #2132 and grabbed a cup to pour some gaterade in and it was already wet, i sniffed my hand and it was 100% urine! The cups are not in plastic like most hotels, so i called the desk. Maria and a security gaurd with 2 housekeepers came to the room, she verified it was in fact urine and removed the cups, had the housekeepers comeback and give the bathroom another quick cleaning and replace the cups. She said she would get me another room but stated they were full and no other rooms are available,  totally understand. But when she said she would compensate us for the trouble and came back with the security gaurd and a $25 gift certificate to Mel's Diner again downstairs,  i declined. We are a family of 5, $25 for urine cups in my room and a bad experience at their diner? I dont they take customer service or their reputation serious enough.

Located in Montgomery Square in Montgomeryville Pa, this is one of the closest Michael's to where I live. As with other Micheals, this store is awesome. This place has so many things for arts and crafts it's like a one stop shop. They have picture frames, candles, toys, and arts and crafts items and so much more! This is the kind of store that interests me, you'll never know what you might find. So if you looking for an awesome place for all your arts and crafts needs this is the place for you!
Horrendous service. Food left at side counter undelivered for over 30 minutes already cold when delivered.

When I go to a deli for a sandwich. I want to order what I want not what some corporate bean counter wants to sell me.
 And their salad bar is all factory farm produced veggies fresh out of a bag or a can.
  Nothing nutritious or organic or even digestable. 
  The place wreaks of corporate control instead of true health concious fare.
Nice store. Good prices. Love the food court and the Starbucks inside. The cashiers are always friendly.
Great atmosphere to enjoy breakfast!  Yummy, cheesy grits but very filling!  One of our favorites when visiting Nola!

We dealt with a guy named Will and purchased a sofa and a chaise. We initially were going to pick it up but decided to have it delivered instead. We called back and set up delivery fees and was charged  $86.50 for it. He said the delivery people would call us the day before and tell us around what time they'd be there for delivery. That never happened so we called Will again and found out he had never actually changed us in the system from pickup to delivery. We were told they could deliver it two days later. I left work on the new day of delivery to let them in and found out they had sent us the sofa and a loveseat instead of the sofa and a chaise that we had ordered. I called the store again and was told they'd have the delivery guys take the love seat back and bring back the chaise. Knowing that'd take over an hour I said I couldn't wait because I needed to go back to work. I was then told "well then you need to call the warehouse and work it out with them".  I asked for the GM and was told he'd call me back. An hour later there was no call so I called him. He listened to all the issues and then rudely said "well what time is good for delivery then?"  He did say he'd refund the delivery charge and when I said I appreciated it but was very upset about the overall experience he replied "sorry bout that, we do aim to please" which seemed pretty sarcastic.  Hopefully the chaise shows up on the next scheduled delivery day so I can be done with this company.
As I stand waiting in line(2nd in line), with one person handling returns, there are 4 others behind desk chatting and laughing and know I'm here waiting. Absurd

Siri led us there by accident and we are glad she did.  It's off the beaten track in the oldest part of Santa Barbara that we had never noticed on our day-cations to the area.  The staff was VERY friendly and attentive.  The lattes we had were QUITE delicious.  So you if you tell Siri "Santa Barbara Coffee Roasters" and get Handlebar instead...give them a try.  P.S.  I thought Handlebar would mean motorcycle bikers, but it means bicycle bikers :O)  Bikers are bikers when it comes to caffeine!

Before I begin my review, DO* NOT* KILL* BEES***

Even if you are allergic!  We depend on them to pollinate.
IF THEY DIE, WE DIE.

But a fly, however...is disgusting.  

Roast his ass.  
Swat him.  
Burn him up.  
Kill him.  
Show no mercy.  

Flies are evil little maggot layers who will literally suck on dead carcass and then have the NERVE to kiss your watermelon.  Lol.  If one lands on your sandwich, please discard that whole part of the sandwich.  Better yet, just discard the whole sandwich.  

You see how much I hate flies?  I was on a mission to find more of the clear sticky window fly trap sheets cause flies are stupid and fly right into them.  They work great, and they can be found here.  Good price for a box of 4.

Now I like this little (slightly confusing) hardware/garden store.  I like how about half of it is outdoors, the other half of the store is indoors.  It has everything you need, but the set-up is a little all over the place.  Once you find out how the store is set up, then you'll remember where most items are located.  But let's say you're from another place and you come here...

You're gonna be like "what the fuck?"  The setup literally makes no sense.  Really.

But the people are helpful and pleasant, it has its own parking lot and the prices are right.  Thank you for carrying the fly traps so that I may continue my crusade against evil flies another day.
Best fried chicken I've had in a very long time. Place looks like an old deli but its definitely worth eating here.

I went yesterday to this cvs location in need of a gas reliever for my newborn and I realized most of the baby medicine (not just gas reliever) was expired and not even from recently but 2 years ago. Please make sure you check the expiration date before buying anything from here, this could be harmful.

Great drinks but really busy for a Tuesday so we didn't get to experience sitting at the carousel bar part. 
My wife had the Pim's cup which was excellent and very refreshing, I highly recommend. I had the Vieux Carre which was great & in my opinion better than a Sazerac because it doesn't have the hint of black licorice taste the Sazerac has.

The burgers here are REALLY good. I got the Gouda burger. It came with basil pesto. I had them put it on the side so I could taste it first, but it was so delicious, I ended up putting it on the burger. I recommend the food for sure.

Ohh, publix. Does anyone else get that overwhelming thought of "I need...EVERYTHING!" After coming into one of these stores? I think I would take a shopping spree here before I would at the mall. Sometimes the way I survive when broke is their BOGO'S(buy one get one). They have everything I want and they are the only grocery store I like to shop at. And they have the best subs in the world(pub philly ftw). Why would you wanna go anywhere else?
Absolutely loved it!  The ambience, food, drinks... all great and surprisingly inexpensive!  This will be a new go-to for my boyfriend and me!

Why did it take me so long to come to this awesome local restaurant?  Let's start with the menu - breakfast is served until 2:00 pm!!!!  That means that those of us who really like to sleep past noon can enjoy a delicious brunch.  Don't worry if you aren't a breakfast person - the lunch menu starts at 11:00 am.  The best of both worlds.  Oh, and there is a bar to be able to enjoy a cocktail (or two or three or whatever you like) with your meal.  Bliss!
Now, let's go to the food - huge portions of tasty goodness are served, and there is a marvelous array of delicious options to choose from.  So darn good!  And the biscuits and gravy are heavenly (and huge).  I enjoyed part of one with my bacon and cheddar omelet, definitely homemade hashbrowns, and toast (I was only able to finish about 1/3 of the entire meal).  My best friend had the #1 breakfast - 2 eggs, 2 sausage links, 2 slices of bacon, hashbrowns, toast, and two massive pancakes.  Everything was served piping hot by a marvelous server.  We were not rushed, and our diet RCs were regularly replenished.
The decor is super cute - the walls are brightly painted with some really cute figures.
So, what are you waiting for?  Go visit this great restaurant and enjoy a great meal!

We had booked a few days in advance and the morning of the tour we got an email saying it was canceled. I am only to assume that they canceled because there was not enough people for the tour, but even if that is the case, we did not see in plain sight a warning or a note when we had made the reservations. We felt duped and disappointed by the company for canceling our tour the way that they did.

So I am only giving 2 stars because the massage was good. I've gone to a variety of massage/spa's so chain ones, others that are local and some provided through a chiropractor to get you to be a patient, lol. Now this place did not scream relaxing or give me an idea it was a spa. The appearance was bad and I went shortly after it had newly open. It literally looks like it was an old office. It doesn't flow and nothing was new. I sat down on a old bench to sign in and wait for someone to come to desk. Yes there is a language barrier, but no big deal to me. The issue I had aside from the bad appearance or lack of, I went in the room and was asked to change, in the middle of getting undressed the lady opens the door without knocking and puts items in the room that I guess she was going to use. Leaves the door open! As I am a little shocked she walks out. I quickly finished getting undressed and as I am about to finish covering my naked body under the sheets she opens the door. Where I notice a man and women seated in maybe what was the waiting area or foot massage section. Literally right across from my room. The room that's right around the corner from the bathroom.  I asked her to quickly close the door. I truly believed this lady did understand modesty and privacy. So I continued on with the massage. She didn't ask if anything hurt or if she should focus on anything. Luckily I was alright but eventually did ask her to focus on neck and shoulders. During the massage I could hear everything outside the door. She left once, leaving the door ajar . Soo when the massage was over, she came back to bring the hot stones she used on me. She must have washed them and put them back in the warmer. I'm like, really? You could wait a minute since I am leaving. The massage was good but the place/vibe didn't feel professional at all. Also they do get you with that "extra tax" that's not paid for on Groupon apparently. I would not recommend, unfortunately.

RUN.... DONT WOK!!! 

Absolutely awesome place to
Grab great Thai food!!

Very cool decor inside, majorly deceiving from the outside!!

Had the Tom Kai coconut soup wow!!!!' To die for!!

They had amazing Pad Thai just the right amount of spice. 
It gets busy around lunch time so early!!

Service is top
Notch!!! 

Love it!!!

We did the voodoo, vampire, witches tour. We had Edward as our guide. He was awesome! Friendly and informative. We checked in 10 min before start time. I think arriving 30 min prior is too long. We stopped at 4 places and he talked about the history and stories. Some of the stories were frightening. In the middle we stopped at a bar if we needed to us the restroom. I noticed towards the end of the tour our group got smaller, oh well. Overall, great tour and experience.

I've visited Tamarind a few times since it took over the old Taste of India location and each time I can say I have been pleased.  Tampa has a few Indian Restaurants, but in my opinion this is the best of the Tampa Bay's offerings.  It's hard to replicate the quality of Indian restaurants in some of the bigger cities in the US, but Tamarind is as close as you will get in the Bay Area.  

My staples here are the seekh kababs and tandoori chicken for appetizers and chicken tikka masala and hariyali chicken for main dishes.  You can't go wrong with any of those choices.  The décor of this restaurant is also pleasant compared to its competitors and they have plenty of wait staff to tend to the needs of its dining guests.

For my sister's wedding we got our hair done here.  There was 1 mother of the bride, 1 bride, 5 bridesmaids.

When scheduling the appointments my sister said there were 5 bridesmaids to get their hair done at 9 but we found out that they scheduled us for 3 girls at 9 and 2 at 10.  Since the photographer was coming at 11 this was a bit stressful.  Also, upon arriving I was told that the lady doing my sister's hair and my hair only accepted cash for the $50 updo.  Not cool especially considering that the only bank in the area was a US Bank and I don't bank there.  I was not impressed with the scheduling or the cash-only thing AT ALL.

However, once we got there they were very welcoming and let us use the empty stylist posts to put on makeup.  They also had coffee and cookies for the customers.  The salon was very clean and the workers friendly.  Also, and probably most importantly, everyone's hair looked awesome the entire day.  

Overall: A-OK.

A neat spot to stop and work for an hour or so with comfortable tables and enough space to spread out your laptop and drink a coffee as you do so.

Of course, the place is *coffee* and *crepes* so in addition to the tasty and creamy latte I enjoyed, I also got one of their breakfast crepes. The "Sunrise Crepe" is scrambled eggs and a meat and some other stuff I can't recall. But the chorizo inside was lightly spicy and the portion size was massive. Do people really eat this much?

Wifi, coffee, food. It was all great.

Prices are a bit high. Me and my friend shared 6 lemon pepper wings and 6 angry wings. The angry wings were not spicy at all, kind of weak and disappointed. THe lemon-pepper was SOOOOO lemon- but I liked it. I wish the wings stayed at least a little crispy, but they got soggy fast.

We also got a side of fries... very very dsiappointing. Soggy, not fresh at all. It wasn't even warm. Fries were just cold and soggy. Did they re-use leftover fries or something? So nasty. And the amount we paid for, we only get a tiny serving. Like a little too tiny it was RIDICULOUS.

I don't know if I would come back for the food, but I liked the happy hour for beer. But that's about it.

We don't live in Reno, but have ordered from here several times for our grandmother during the pandemic. The delivery people have always been great and communicative. Food is always delicious and grandma is happy!

Needed to get some Fromm Dog food and needed to have curb side service.  Answered right away and had the food I needed for my Westie.  They made the purchase very easy.  Later when I went to pick up the food that I had ordered it was ready and out to my car quickly.  This is going to be my new local store as the other one I had used for years was open but not responsive to calls.  Thank you!!!

oh snap!! what a surprise this was - looks like your typical neighborhood mom & pop joint - which I like mind you - casual atmosphere, friendly greeter, friendly staff... expecting the food to be good - but it was AWESOME!!! I had seafood stuffed eggplant -Ooooo Myyyy GOSH!!! 2 medallions of eggplant & in the middle seafood stuffing layered w/ some kind of awesome sauce - & BIG OLE shrimps on top & side FRIKKIN' YUM! My Honey had shrimp ettouffee & you figure small shrimp in a buttery sauce - these shrimp were HUGE!!! & it was TASTY!!! OH!!! & we had onion rings to start (that should have clued us in the very beginning that this was going to special - the seasoning on the onion rings wasn't JUST your typical fry batter stuff - there were herbs & spices in it YUM!!!!! (oh & did I mention ... NOT FIGURE FRIENDLY - well at least what I ate...) 
The place is very nice neighborhood type restaurant - nicely painted, good atmosphere, great staff!

Even after their expansion, UBB still runs out of seating, which serves as a testament to the quality of patrons' coffee experience. On an average day, you'll see the entire space occupied by college students studying with a cup of coffee and a sandwich. The wooden interior matches the free-trade ethos of the company. It's a chill ambience and an ideal work to hammer out a paper. 

I do most of my coffee chats here because of the pleasant environment. Sometimes drinks take a while to be made so patience is required. Definitely take time to enjoy the experience.
Fabulous place. Clean, beautiful, best customer service I've ever received at a salon. Tons of color choices! Will visit every time I'm in Philly!

The BEST paws down! Took last minute appointments, super friendly, and great prices! Not to mention turn over time was amazing. I wasn't waiting around for hours, wondering what is my dog doing. I would totally recommend to everyone! Traveled from FL 

Will totally bring my pooch back!

I really WANT to like Ron's, and I do enjoy the little bar with the great beer selection...but every time I go there something is disappointing.  

So... being a native Texan, I have very particular tastes in BBQ,so it should have come as no surprise that the ribs were just eh, but not awful.  What was awful that visit were the two LONG hairs I found in the beans, YUCK.  

On our next visit, I tried to stick with something more reliable like pizza - plain old pepperoni pizza.  But the one food group I hate is the Onion Family.  For some reason, they put onions on my pizza!  No big deal but I had to pick them off before I could eat them.

Our next visit was just to the bar to watch a band play.  We thought about eating, but when you look through a 10 page menu and NOTHING looks appetizing you know you need to move on.  A couple of suggestions:  cut the menu down to two or three genres instead of eight and for heaven's sake, don't charge so much money to substitute a potato side for a vegetable side!  

Why did I keep going back?  Because my husband's business is located about 1/2 a mile away and it's convenient. But honestly, we've been avoiding it lately until we hear that the menu is changing. 

I will check back in a few months and hopefully can raise the rating to 3 stars.

"Door to Narnia"

This is the epitome of what a massage space should be.  Once you enter through the door you are instantly transformed...and by you, I mean all of you.  All of your senses are touched from the moment you enter and you can instantly feel your stress level decrease.  Andrew has created a space that speaks of the experience awaiting you on the table.  He sits with you before the massage to determine your problem areas, address them during the treatment and checks in periodically during to make sure the session is advancing as you expected.  Thank you for your dedication and for providing a perfect sanctuary.

Great, fast service and a lot of excellent flavors! I couldn't believe some of them were frozen yogurt and not ice cream! Wednesday they have a waffle cone special, it's definitely worth it even though it's a 20 minute drive for us. A quick note that it's on the end Of the strip mall, as we had a hard time locating it at first from the road we came in on. It's right near the entrance off of Maple, across the entrance to Dunkin' Donuts and Trainos.
best manicures in st. petersburg! Holly always does the best job, and my nails always look amazing. Very professional and just a great place to support.

Honestly its a tale of two restaurants. The bar itself is excellent with a knowledgeable staff and varied local and international brews. However the food and restaurant itself is the very definition of "hit or miss". Food and service can vary between delicious and attentive to stomach churning and poor. The bar is a solid 4/5 whereas the rest is a 2/5.

Ambiance: Dark and divey that has a definite "hipster" vibe. Lots of dark woods throughout, but can feel surprisingly open depending on time of day (natural light helps a lot). The bar area can seat about 20, whereas the dining room can hold about 30 or so. There is also a subtle but pervasive smell of stale beer throughout, which actually makes things better for some odd reason.

Food: You will either have a great meal or a terrible one, with hardly no in between. The broccoli rabe and brussel sprouts are delicious when done right, but can occasionally be so heavily salted you feel like you are chewing on a salt cube. The chili oil on the brussel sprouts is a nice touch, but again buyer beware. I would stay away from the seitan nuggets, they were dry and over-spiced. 

Service: Once again, the bar shines. I can walk in with a vague description of what I want, and the bartender can find the perfect beer for me. The waiters and waitresses can vary between surly and pleasant. Sometimes it seems that my mere existence is a burden to the staff (several times I have waited about 30 minutes to order my food. Just let me give you my money!) 

Drinks: Their local beer selection is quite large, but they still have several international beers (typically Belgian). What I love the most is the incredibly varied styles they serve. Typically you can find you standard IPAs or lagers, but also more exotic styles like wild ales, barrel-aged brews, or various tripels. They do have enough liquor to make a good old-fashioned, but don't expect any crazy cocktails though.

The employees had a pizza returned by one customer that was opened up in their car. They then tried to remove the broken seal and install a new seal like the pizza was never touched and taken outside of the store. They were then again watched trying to give that pizza to another customer. (Completely disgusted). The owner called today and had the worst attitude and didn't seem to care just said sorry for the mistake. Bad business owner and employees who dont care about food and health safety especially during the Covid 19 Pandemic.

I was staying in the hilton and the closest non hotel breakfast was right across the street! 

Grabbed some breakfast to-go here. I had the belgian waffle, the home fries, and the philly cheesesteak omelette. The reviews were raving about a coconut syrup and that stuff is super sweet but super GOOD! 

The real highlight was the philly omelette!! Its just perfect. Full of deliciously cooked beef and just made perfect. Order it!!!

Turchetti's was awesome. We went on my lunch break, arrived around noon. It is pretty small but has a lot of 2 top tables and surprisingly many tables were open. I will say most these tables quickly filled up around 12:30 though. The food was so good! I had the turkey sandwich, which lasted me two lunches, with the chips which were the homestyle, the kind you know are fresh. My husband got Rosino, with chips also, his was good but mine was the show stopper. We ordered at the counter and the food came out promptly. The only reason I gave it 4 stars is the price. 2 sandwhiches with 2 cans of diet cokes, netted us over $30 which seems a bit excessive for lunch with sandwiches, but it is about average for the area. Overall great spot and phenomenal food!
I love first watch! The chimichanga is very delicious!  The greeter was very friendly.
Absolutely  love this place!!! Food was great. The quinoa soup is a must have. The turkey BLT is decent. It's a good spot to meet up and hang out. The low calorie selections are tasty.

Came into walgreens about 15 minutes ago, picked up prescription and got a heating pad some vitamins and toy with my wife, got to the registers and the woman working at 1:10am December 29th with brats earrings, SOUR attitude, rude, unprofessional and un-attentive. Went to the register, I noticed nobody was there, but there was things being rung up at the register, asked if someone was ahead of me, got ignored while the woman was on her cell phone, cursing with another associate, while scrolling on her phone and ignoring us, we got to the register, she rang our things up, my wife and I were checking the screen for a deal on vitamins for her heart and wanted to make sure they were BOGO, all while the woman was getting impatient and frustrated that we were just checking to see how the BOGO worked, and told me wife, " you have to buy the same bottle, to get BOGO, with a sour attitude told her " IF YOU CAN EVEN UNDERSTAND THAT." And then bagged our things, got back on her cell phone and we picked our bags up after paying from the actual bag metal holder. 

If you hate your job that badly, or act that unprofessional you should be fired. Absolutely not an excuse to act like this in a store. LET ALONE YOUR JOB, LET ALONE TO STRANGERS PICKING UP THEIR PRESCRIPTION.

Wanted to put zero stars. The bartender rolled his eyes at me. The fat bald one with a beard. My wings came out ice cold and soggy. Who serves soggy wings?? This guy apparently. Then proceeds to tell the other bartender that I'm a complainer. Really!!? You served me soggy wings! Second time I have been here and same thing happens. Avoid like the plague. The bar is dirty And not wiped down. Completely unexceptionable! If you can't run a bar with 2 other bartenders.. please quit and look for employment elsewhere.
I ordered a 6 piece chicken tender box and got 4 good pieces and 2 pieces that were smaller than a chicken nugget and had no chicken. Not worth $7 at all.

Please don't trust their online scheduling. I made an appointment for 8-1 for them to come to my home and got a confirmation. I was called at 11:30 to say the tech was running late. I called back to say I had to leave my home at 2:45, and the phone agent told me the tech was on his way. Great! I then got a call back that the tech was confused and was NOT on his way and would not make it on time. So now I wasted a morning and possibly risked my windshield being damaged further. Very frustrating.

One again I got screwed from this guy.   Had a radon service test by him and stucco inspection and other repairs to my home. Total unprofessional owner. They quote you a price and send you a bill for more than triple the quote.  You call and complain and the owner Rob yells and curses at you on the phone saying he doesn't leave his house for work for under a $1000 job.   Worst yet, his work and inspections are terrible. I had to bring another company in to fix his and his employees mistakes .   I would never use company again.  Please stay away from this guy and use a reputable company

My wife and I bought a smaller home and knew when we moved in that old windows needed replaced.  We contacted Window Nation and ordered 4 new windows.  We paid half the cost then and the remaining half after most of the installation was completed.  We were told by the installer that the trim boards around the windows needed to be replaced and it did take us several weeks to get that done.  When Window Nation came back out to complete the work the installer said they could not complete the work because of the new trim they had told us we needed to have replaced.  As such, they have not completed the job even though we fully paid for the work months ago.  While the windows are very nice my experience with long delays in getting all work done including window screens that weren't delivered for weeks makes my wife and I hesitant to do business with this company again.

I love this place!!! It's pretty close to work so it makes for an easy lunch. I haven't had dinner here yet but I do at least come here once a week.... sometime twice when I can't control myself. It never gets old.

Firstly, the server is always awesome. He's typically quick, attentive, and by now remembers what we usually order. 

The lunch menu is straight to the point and I like that. It has just enough options for some variety yet you don't get bored. It's a great price for the lunch specials. I also enjoy the sushi menu!

The food!! Is amazing. My favs have to be the Pad Kee Mao and the Pad Thai. My go to sushi is the fried Philly roll. The entree comes with soup and a salad and they are really good about subbing out either one with steamed rice if you like.

This is definitely a spot worth checking out!
Excellent place for authentic Mexican.  Don't miss the Guacamole San Jose.  It is simply awesome.

We had the most amazing time. Kendra is an absolute Kick ass host. She literally did the whole party for me. I was able to just sit back and watch my sons party and enjoy everything. Definitely a first for me . Great venue kids had a blast money well spent. Thanks Kendra you ROCK

Just moved into my new house and had some major plumbing issues. After doing tons of research and combing through tons of reviews, I made my decision to go with Roman Plumbing. I never had to hire a plumber let alone shell money out for a plumber and for all the work they did, I say it was a fair price for the professionalism and the customer service that was provided, its hard these days to find a good reliable company. When I called and spoke to Mindy I knew right away I wanted to schedule, but before I did, I made one more call. When I called back, I spoke to a very nice gentleman and he scheduled me right in. My main water valve to the house was leaking, they sent Zach out, I had a very pleasurable experience with him. Its nice having techs come out to your home and make you feel comfortable. I had to call Roman back out again, but this time it was a Saturday. They sent William right out, again another pleasurable experience. William was very knowledgeable and very kind. I do recommend getting the Roman promise, as it could save you a few dollars down the road, because after my first call I didn't realize, I would need them back out again. Defiantly a company you can trust. Don't hesitate or waste anymore time, go with Roman!

I am a huge sweets person and I will say the giant oversized cake slices are just what any dessert eater needs.  Its 2lbs of the best thing youll ever put in your mouth.  The cookies however are sub par. BEst cakes=coconut lemon, german chocolate and the strawberry cheesecake. AMAZING!!!!!

Love the rolls they have there and with the butter, mmmmmmm. I come here all the thine for steaks which are delicious. one complain is the Caesar Salad, sometimes it's loaded with dressing, other times there's not enough of it. Also sometimes I get the ends of the romaine lettuce which doesn't make the salad to appetizing. Other wise great location and food for a chain restaurant.

Great service! But the feng shui in this place needs some work, the seating is rather compressed. Three of the four of us in our party are 6' or taller and it was...uncomfortable. Typical tasty and quick ihop fare, Maria is a fantastic server, great experience.

Maybe it's simply not for me, but I really don't understand the popularity of this place. Overpriced, overrated, and Tex-Mex is such a tired concept. I've been here twice with 2 different groups of people. The food wasn't necessarily terrible, but it certainly wasn't anything I'd ever want to revisit. Perhaps it's more of a tourist draw, as the environment seems very much geared towards the late night socialite kind of person.
Been looking for a breakfast spot like this for a while. Solid, consistent food and always friendly service!

My beau and I went here for brunch after a bike ride. The atmosphere is on point and the food is awesome. He's always bugging me to go back. I had the chicken and waffles (drooled a little when I just typed that). Yum. Hidden gem in the quarter.

Disappointing experience because my boyfriend called in advance to let the restaurant know that he is a vegetarian and would want a tasting menu (as the website says that they love cooking for vegetarians and to let them know in advance). We actually got engaged that day, and thus that was one of the reasons why he had called in advance.  He called about 2 weeks in advance.  When we get there, they let us know that there is nothing different for vegetarians and he would have to pick whats off of the menu.  We most likely would not have come here had they not said that they could make something special for vegetarians.  

I am not  vegetarian and got a 3 course tasting menu.  Food was ample for 3 courses, anything more would have been too much.  Most likely wont be back
Jon at Stars and Stripes is going over and above to help get much needed tools to Haiti to help local kids, who are part of the Haiti Marine Project, learn to build fishing boats.

I've dined here three times in six weeks and will continue to sample the menu before awarding five stars. They're on target for that goal. Pizza, veal parmigiana and spaghetti w/meatballs all have been tasty, hot and well presented. Garlic bread is toasted with a butter/olive oil concoction that is a real treat.

Victoria, is a no nonsense waitress that does the work of three. I prefer her direct approach and rely on her suggestions. If you're expecting to be greeted with, "hello, my name is Sissy and I'll be your server," this is NOT your type of restaurant. Go to State Street.

The head cook (not sure of his name - the guy with blac framed glasses in the photo) is the commander-in-chief of the kitchen which, by the way, is in full view of the bar. No secrets here just sensational cooking.

After some hesitation from the reviews we read we decided to check the place out. We were pleasantly surprised by the clean venue and courteous staff. The venue isn't super big but still a kid pleaser for sure.  Laser tag here was by far the best thing this place has going for it. The multi level arena was awesome and lots of fun.  When we visit Tucson again we will be back.

I had a hard time finding an artist I really liked in Philly, as soon as I walked in Tony was professional and kind. He seemed to understand exactly what I wanted and clearly spent a lot of time on the design. He clearly has passion for what he does- I'll absolutely be going back for another tattoo soon!

Great guys and the food is awesome but they need to stop telling people 30-35 minutes when the wait is over an hour. If this was just a one-off I could understand but I see this pretty regularly on Saturdays at Clark Park. If it's going to be an hour or an hour and a half, just tell people that. It turns into people walking up to the truck every 5 minutes asking when their order will be ready, complaining about it, and then getting their food before others that were waiting a half hour longer. I'll keep eating here but I wish they were more realistic with customers when they're busy.

Pastor burrito (spicy) is LEGIT. Haven't strayed to much else besides the chicken  (also tasty).

I couldn't be happier. I know I needed my interior painted and that was all I knew. Al helped me decide on what colors to go with and was very accommodating with the timeline. The guys who painted very professional, courteous and I could not be happier with the end result. I highly recommend them

My family & I order from here ALOT because their food is so yummy!! The staff is kind, courteous and thorough. Delivery seems to be the thing now  a days, so I'd like to add that our delivery has been on point every time. So if you are looking for great food & smoothies that are healthy for ya here's your spot.
Over priced.   New Orleans fish was hard and dry.  Hostess and waiter aloof.  Would not ever go back.

Poor service, two shawarma platters took 30+ minutes. One paying customer walked out of the restaurant without food because they said "nothing was ready right now." Overpriced food with fees hidden in the menu. $34 for two shawarma because rice and hummus were $4 add ons. Don't waste your time or money here, much better restaurants in West Philly.
I love that it's never crazy busy when we go, everyone is very polite and friendly, and no complaints on the food!

Please go here and eat here... Often. I have a horrible track record of my favorite places closing down. This is one of my favorite places in Tampa... Food is great, service is always perfect, great for watching sports, great beer as well as the fru fru cocktails. Nice atmosphere, outdoor seating available. Let's see... What else? Oh yeah! Clean bathrooms! Give it a visit...i think you'll like it.

There are many ghost tours in the French Quarter and we happened to choose the Ghost and Vampire tour originating from the Voo Doo Lounge and were very pleased. Our guide's name was Lee and he was awesomely entertaining with the ability to tell a well balanced story of the macabre with humor. We walked by several other groups and clearly we had the best of the lot. The other tour company guides seemed to have a lack of enthusiasm and passion. Lee shared very interesting ghost and vampire stories of New Orleans rich history with his tongue in cheek humor, which kept us going through such a long walk. Many thanks to Lee's and the group for their patience on waiting for the old folks. If Lee had been dull at all, we would have bailed on the tour, because we were hurting.

My husband and I have been there a couple times and haven't had a bad experience yet.  It's hard to find a place that has a decently priced happy hour with good food and this is definitely the place.  They have a couple $3 beers and good $5 appetizers, including pizza.  

We got out of there this last time with full bellies and a buzz for $20.  Its really hard to find a place like this off the Main Line but we are lucky to have it in our neighborhood.

Wow! I've walked by this spot often, and upset now about the decision to that....this is the best Italian in the area! Excellent food, atmosphere, and people.  So if you ever wonder where to go, head to this gem in Phoenixville.  You will not be disappointed...menu has a lot of options, and that may be your hardest choice. Regardless of the direction, you will appreciate your first decision of going here!  Great job and look forward to the next time.

I just picked up my car from its first experience at Costa's.  I have a 2012 Audi Q5 which I've always taken to the dealer.  The warranty expired last year however, and the dealer maintenance at Wynnewood Audi is outrageous. I took the car in for an oil change and state inspection for which I paid $189 at Costa's and they told me the car was in great shape otherwise.  For the same maintenance last year at the dealer I paid over $800 and didn't even do all that they recommended.  I'll keep updating as I continue to take my car to Costa's for regular maintenance and repair.

I recently purchased a used car from Derrick Dodge Edmonton. I found the experience was over all very good. I had never bought/financed a car through a dealership before and because of that, I was feeling overwhelmed. The sales staff took the time to answer all of my questions and make sure I understood everything. They delivered the car to me on the day promised, and at the time they promised (Always a bonus!) and the car arrived fully detailed and inspected, needed an oil change and that was is it. The only complaint I had was that I found a small tear in the back seat pocket but that's a minor detail. They even phoned a few days later to ask about my satisfaction with everything. Over all I had a good experience and would recommend them to anybody looking at buying a well priced used car, or a new car.

Haven't made a Yelp review in a long time, but I had to say something about this place. Came here on a weeknight and sat inside. It was pretty quiet so we were able to enjoy each others company and music. Our waitress, Terry, took care of us like we were in her own home. Our food from start to finish was amazing. I highly recommend the blackened maji fish tacos! And they only have one desert item, their key lime pie which was probably the best of its kind I've ever had! Overall perfect night!

I am very happy I chose this company to move! I had quite a bit of furniture and boxes to move and this group of young men were so great! They were efficient but yet very careful not to damage any of my belongings or the apartment. They arrived on time and were very professional and I would be thrilled to use them again! I havent always had the best luck moving, so this was a pleasant experience. After today, I know if I move again in Philadelphia in the future, they are my first pick.

Could be the best place for a pedi that I've ever experienced in NOLA. The salon is clean and the guy who did my nails was very attentive to my personal needs. I felt the service was worth the fee and he spent almost an hour from start to finish on my nails. It was exactly the pampering I had in mind. 

Thank you!

First time coming here after being recommended from my bro, and I was not disappointed the staff was so nice and helpful. Explained the contents of the meals very well. The drinks were perfectly chilled and the food was next level good. I don't normally eat collard greens outside of my own home but these were seasoned great and had ham hocks and bacon in it omg. The chicken sandwich was so husky bun was super soft with the crunchy chicken great bite. I will be back many more times
Staff - not friendly. Place- hard to find if you're not local. Food - just be hungry. Good chocolate shake.

If Pat's or Gino's us your favorite steak, you're not from Philly.  John's is amazing.  Steak was brilliant and the roast pork even better.  I wouldn't do the sharp cheese in the steak again, but overall, a big huge thumbs up and the best I've had in Philly.  Sorry Jim's.

Best shop in the city, and honestly one of the best I've been to period.

When I moved to Philly I was unsure of where to get my comics and a friend recommended me here and I've never looked back. Rob and Brian are nice, and knowledgable. The shop itself has tons of variety, and it's easy to spend WAY too much money here. It's one of my constants. I don't know what I'd do without this place.
I went here specifically for the gyros. They are worth stopping by to check out. I recommend take out because you actually get more for your money. I will update again after my next visit.

I was excited to try The Blue Tortilla since I always pass it in New Hope but had never stopped. My brother and I decided to stop in on a beautiful day for lunch. There were only two couples out on the patio so we got to choose any seat. There is no water views here. If you want to sit on the water then the landing restaurant is delicious and right next door. The service at a The Blue Tortilla was pleasant but a bit on the slow side for everything despite the place being empty. The menu isn't very big and the prices are a bit high for what you get. My brother paid $12.95 for a basket of chips, salsa and guacamole. Everyone passing commented on the chips. They are delicious but not cheap! The guacamole and salsa was delicious and this is probably the only thing I would come bac for. However for the price I would definitely have to think about it. I got the crispy chicken tacos. They were good but definitely not out of this world and certainly not worth the $17 I paid. Three rolled up chicken tacos with some lettuce on top, a side of beans and a side of rice. Rice and beans were bland. All in all it was an okay experience but I probably wouldn't come back. There's other places in new hope with cheaper prices, better food and better views.

I have heard such great things about this place and am hoping my visit was not the norm. I came in December but just noticed my review didn't post then.

Nothing is worst than Burnt pizza! Shame on us for not sending it back but my husband believes you shouldn't do that, plus after we got our pizzas there was a very long line. They also forgot to cut one of the pizzas so I had to go back and they ended up cutting it in all different uneven sizes. I threw my pizza away after the first slice since I could not get past the burnt taste.

The restroom was completely disgusting. The men's was out of order so there was only one restroom. The floors were completely soaked, toilet paper and paper towels were all over the ground. It was like the place exploded! When we were leaving I felt for the gal who was cleaning the restroom.

Went to the Burlesque Ballyhoo.  The two hosts are pretty funny, and the girls are amazing.  The whole scene is pretty awesome.  Everyone is friendly and the bar is well stocked.  They mostly (possibly only) have premium liquor, but the price on their liquor is fair.  They also have drink specials and some recipes exclusive to their theater.  

I will definitely be back.  Thanks for a great time!

Came to The Depot with a friend, ostensibly for drinks but stayed for food because the menu is so enticing. We enjoyed a delightful set of cornbread fritters (guiltily good) tempered with Brussel sprouts & bacon. Perfect pairing with their IPA.

The staff are super-friendly and accommodating. 

Looking forward to coming back!

I came in to the Santa Barbara location today for the 'service after the sale'. So often part of a sales pitch is all the service you'll receive later if you need it. Well, today I needed it and the tires were purchased months ago. I came in for the free rotation and had a couple of other concerns. I was incredible happy with being treated with the same attention and urgency as if I was writing the check today. My bill today was $0 and the service was great. Experiences like this creates a long-term customer.

Thanks for the help.
wasn't what i expected, thinly breaded and was expecting a much greater breading, maybe it's just me

Absolutely try a bowl but don't miss out on the avocado toast. I feel like avocado toast is often overhyped but this avocado toast was a surprise hit with salty bits, pepperoncini, pickled onions, watermelon radish, and micro greens. Totally delicious!!

We loved the food here, however I felt that the tables were too small for the size of their dishes. It's also family sized. They take cash and Venmo which is nice! Rice is not included with the dishes but you'll often need it. The pictures I took were after we had begun eating, so the portions are A LOT larger than reflected in the picture.

Nice enough ambiance - looks very promising on first glance, but the food and service were a huge disappointment. I ordered the steak sandwich because of the promising ingredients (I like strongly seasoned dishes) but was SMACKED in the face with a single note - BEEF. Chewy, chewy beef. 
This was especially disappointing because I was torn between several sandwiches. The waitress, however, was disinterested and absent almost our whole meal (the bus person was diligent and pleasant) and completely uninterested in addressing the questions I had about the choices. 
Would definitely not come again and would recommend skipping it.
Great rooftop bar perfect for a night out with friends! Went for a bachelorette party had an amazing experience in a private area with great service, music and ever better drinks!

Sloooow service...saw the water boy 3 times before the waiter. Four of us finished our meal before our 6th guest's meal arrived. Food was not worth the wait. Of course the check took a while, and then the waiter stood over me as I added tip and signed check...for the last time.

I eat meat but I'm not a meat head. Be that as it may, I came here just to compare it to Chima really. I went to chima 1.5yrs ago.

I'll get right to it
-Nice ambience
-I didn't really like the salad bar. Probably because it was truly a salad bar...I think the Chima salad bar had more variety and I enjoyed that one more.
- Meal was just meat upon meat upon meat...not much to say about that. I get full easily so I asked for some pieces at a time. I def enjoyed the meat but I am not wired to go overboard like most people can. 
-I had unlimited supply of wine so I def filled up on that. 
-Dessert was nothing special. I had the cheesecake truffle. But by that time i was soo stuffed and tipsy i just couldn't stand myself.

Finally glad I visited this place. I don't think it's particularly any better than Chima (chima's salad bar is better tho) so I would recommend both places, for meat, equally. 
I went to Chima during restuarant week so that was $35.

My Fogo meal was a freebie so not sure how much damaged i did (esp with the unlimited wine I was exposed to)...loved it!

This one's for the guys. Every man has had a bad haircut at least one time in his life and there's nothing that makes.you look worse. Today I had my hair cut at details by Oliver. Oliver is a very experienced Master Barber. It was a joy to watch him perform his craft on my hair. Oliver has much pride in his work and is meticulous about how he does your hair. This was the best haircut experience that I have had in my lifetime. So if you want a good haircut I suggest you check out details and Oliver
Quick response. Competitive pricing. Friendly customer service. Easy to make an appointment. Hoping not to need the service again however would recommend the services.

For cheap sporting goods it's the place to go. For quality sporting goods and customer service it's not. If you want some stuff for a weekend away and don't want or need new stuff this is the place for you

We had my daughter's birthday party at Prime 1000 tonight and everything was excellent.  The service, the food, the waiter, etc.  They made sure everything was perfect.  A big shout out to Tom for making sure everything was great!!!

When i checked into my hotel in New Orleans late last night I was excited to learn that Dickie Brennan's Bourbon House was inside the hotel facility.  With the Brennan family's reputation for fine food I was looking forward to a better meal than I usually get in hotel restaurants. So after eating there was it better?  Yes, but not by much.  The physical layout is big..Disney big.  The space swallowed the party of twenty in front of me without even putting a dent in the normal flow of the restaurant.  But that size makes it difficult to get that New Orleans feel in spite of he wrought iron used throughout the decor.  The service was crisp and efficient, a good thing but perhaps aimed more at moving the customers through to maximize table turns.  

My drink was very good....I've become a real fan of the Sazzerac and the Bourbon House lived up to their name with dynamite version.  Just the right combo of ingredients.  The  gumbo was only so-so...loaded with shrimp and two huge oysters....but it lacked the depth of flavor that marks a great gumbo.  The special appetizer of sweetbreads with crawfish was very good....the sweetbreads were crispy on the outside yet retained the creaminess on the inside and the deep rich sauce with the crawfish was a nice contrast without overpowering the sweetbreads. My Bourbon House salad was just OK. ..a very basic salad.  Being a sucker for anything that's listed "best of" I had to try their Milk Punch that was listed in the dessert menu as  voted the best in New Orleans.  It was very good but again it seemed like a Disney version of the real thing...lacking that true New Orleans character...pretty much like the whole restaurant.

Wow! Dinner was amazing from the oysters, tuna tartar, and filet.   What a perfect night.   They are going to give the other steak restaurants a run for their money.  Kevin was our waiter and he couldn't have been better.   We are already looking at scheduling our next dinner.

Only two stars for the paraffin wax for the pedicure. The actual application of the polish was HORRIBLE! She got polish all over my skin and was trying to wipe it off with her nails. Just a very rushed and sloppy job!

My fiancé and I were driving by and thought lets have some bagel sandwiches for breakfast. When we walked in the line was to the back of the door, so we thought this place had to be good. 

We ordered a cup of coffee, blueberry Cheesecake muffin, southern tradition with ham on an asiago cheese bagel and ranchero breakfast bagel on jalapeño bagel.

We found a seat, chose a coffee from their variety of flavored coffee selections and waited for them to bring out our sandwiches. They yell your name to pick up your muffin. The muffin was good. 

When the sandwiches arrived they didn't appear very fresh, I had the ranchero, the jalapeños on the sandwich looked like they were out of a can, my sandwich temperature was an issue because the cheese wasn't even melted.  My fiancées sandwich was much better. 

All in all we were not impressed, we prefer Einstein Bagels.
Best place for Vietnamese food! They also carry Chinese food! We love to mix and match! The pho bowls are our favorite!
Great coffee and atmosphere.  As a bonus, there's free wifi and enough outlets for you to charge dozens of electronics.

This is my favorite yoga studio, period. The staff is friendly, there are always generous offerings in the reception area, a great selection of books, inspiring art on the walls.....the list goes on. 

I've been going to Kendall's class, and it's awesome. She delivers a class that is creative in it's sequencing, with a fun atmosphere and an emphasis on finding 'what work's best for you', and she has great playlists too.  I also felt like she was looking out for my safety, where she offered intermediate alternatives while teaching advanced, level 3 poses. 

I like the fact that she's also naturopathic doctor. I find comfort in knowing my yoga teacher understands how the body works, and she mentioned how her 'alignment based yoga' is done in an order that is best for the human body from a medical/anatomical perspective. 

Yoga Soup has earned my business by hiring the knowledgable, excellent teachers, and providing a wonderful service. Thank you for being part of the SB community, and I highly recommend it to anyone looking for a class.
The service here sucked.. the sad part is that it was not busy.  Our server was super slow.  The food was cold and nasty.  I had to ask for a refill because she never offered.  Not worth the money..

If I could rate this place with negative stars, it still would be too good. This Enterprise has the worst customer service ever. Ashley Hinds( so-called assistant manager) is rude, unprofessional, incompetent, and lair. Made a reservation for a compact Nissan for 3 days at $27+, it was confirmed by an email, confirmation number, and I even called this branch and confirmed with Harrison day before pick-up. 

On the day of pick up, Ashley Hinds look up my reservation and mysteriously my compact Nissan turns into an F-150 XLT pickup reservation. I told her, no I have a Nissan. I provided her confirmation and email. She said that's wrong and we don't have that reservation for a Nissan . That I was wrong. I try to show her the email and provided the confirmation number, she wasn't having it. Putting me in a bad position I say I'll take the F-150he price that was promised to me for the Nissan. She instantly became defenses said no I can't do that. I said that we have a problem I have a reservation and a confirmation for a set price and now you're trying to triple my quote. Ashley kept on saying you're wrong you modified it. I said let me talk to your branch manager, and she was in charge of the branch. (More lies)

This is the point were the stand still came into play. Where she claims that she was scare and uncomfortable renting to me at this point and threatened to call the police. I told her, go ahead and waited patiently for Pasco County sheriff's office to arrive. This is the point when her other black co-worker got invovled, also rude unprofessional. Ask "what are you still doing here"? I said I'm waiting for the police.Yes, the lying incompetent Ashley Hinds called the police. 30mins + later the police showed up and heard both sides. I provided the officer with my email stating the price and Nissan, not F150. They looked at the email and instantly knew something was wrong. 

10 mins later after the police arrived, magically Ashley found the Nissan reservation. Probly the point of back peddling for Ashley, because of my email. This is They offered the F150 for the quoted price. Which I asked in the very beginning. So it takes police involvement, 3 wasted hours to fix this solution. All Ashley Hinds had to do was read the email. But caught in a lie and try to up sell me and she was too cowardly to apologize. I guess she wasn't scared to rent the vehicle after all. Holly the only polite professional person took over and completed the reservation. 

So my advice is to stay far away from this branch, Ashley Hinds and the other black female co-worker (didn't get her name and I don't care to know either). You will waste your time, have the police called on you, and have your reservation either canceled or an upgraded vehicle at triple the price. 

Ashley Hinds gives females a bad name. Plays that card when someone points out a mistake. Instantly claim she scared, I'm not honoring that "you're wrong and I'm calling the police. 

If you want to see the email confirmation for the Nissan and the police information of the officer involved free so free to contact me.

Been here a bunch because it's close by. Why don't they post the name of the movie outside the individual theater like they did ten plus years ago? I'm too busy juggling popcorn and butterfinger bites to remember what theater my movie is in or to get into my pocket to check. This has happened multiple times I feel like I can't be the only one.

Also, they really need to fill the popcorn halfway then add butter so the bottom half isn't dry when I top it off at the end. On the plus side, they have a never ending supply of napkins so my fingers aren't buttery. Two stars, same color as the butter they should put in the half full popcorn.
Donuts are obviously fresh and still warm from cooking. Sandwiches took a little but we're still good.

I was extremely pleased with the service this company gave. They were on time for a back and forth trip between the airport and Murfreesboro, TN. When I called after arriving at the airport, the drive/owner immediately answered and told me exactly where to go for the shuttle area. I ran into a friend who was also going to the same conference and I asked the driver if she could come along. Because he had room in the van, he said yes and she paid a fee less than if she had taken another form of transportation. On the return trip, I felt completely comfortable in the fan by myself with the driver. If I return to Nashville airport, I will again call on this shuttle service.

Stopped in for half price sushi. Well... nothing here was GREAT!  There's nothing to write home about. We tried 5 different rolls as well as the ramen!  The ramen was TASTELESS!  I expressed this to our waitress and I was told, "this is more traditional". Well... I've had a lot of ramen, and this was the worst by far. Waitress was very nice and helpful, however, we didn't stop in for company we stopped in for the food. We won't be back.

Well golly ! We loved this place ! Everything was a good price and tasted great ! Cool vibes and great service. Large portions and fun! Gonna try and go here on the regular. Fajitas and cheese dip! Mmmm

I highly recommend! We ordered delivery and it was fast and delicious. This place is amazing if you are looking for sushi, and especially if you want to customize, get the build your own bowl. Yum! Thank you!
Had a great time with my sister. Service , food and drinks were fantastic. The papas bravas were delicious. A little pricy but well worth it.
I only had a zipper replaced on a pair of jeans, but they did a great job with them. Price was pretty good.

I'd recommend BK's over El Guerro Canelo anytime! The carne asada is some of the best you'll find. It's juicy and cooked to perfection, includes a full salsa bar. Where just about anything you want to put on your burros and taco's is included. The shrimp taco's are terrible, though. It's just 2 grocery store breaded shrimp on a small tortilla. That's it. Now, my fiance loves the things and gets them everytime, but I would stick to the Sonoran hot dogs and carne asada. The hot dogs are better than El Guerro Canelo and the restaurant is a perfect for dinner. It's an actual sit down restaurant, the waitresses are cute, and friendly, and the service is great. Prices aren't bad either, but I'm a big guy and always order 3 or more hot dogs and a burrito and wish the hot dogs weren't $2. If they ever had a special and they were $.99, I'd eat them everyday and nothing else until the special was over! Plus beers are cheap! Take the guys out and order a bunch of beers and a bunch of hot dogs and you're in for a great time!  Open late.

This was a really cute chill spot for dessert and bubble tea. I took a few of my out of town friends here on a "walking tour" in the city. I really liked how each seating area is a bit sectioned off so you can have some privacy. 

Once we arrived we were immediately seated and we ordered through their website on our phones. That was pretty convenient since we could browse, select our choices and pay separately. More restaurants need to do this!!

They had a lot of optioned to choose from. I ended up selecting the molten lava cake with vanilla ice cream. It was pretty good but if I come back, I'd definitely choose a crepe cake my my friends did!
Best gyros around! The pita bread is always so fresh, warm, & delicious and their hummus is great too!

Great service across the board. Maximo in reception was awesome as were the folks taking care ofe on the roof.

Great service, views, I'm looking forward to coming back.

Now that Bootleggin BBQ is at the Pour House, it has some of the best food you can get in downtown STL. The sampler platter with ribs and burnt ends is spectacular. Also the house made chips are to die for.
Awesome Pho. Very good service and atmosphere. My 3rd time here and I'm still not disappointed. Good place

Oh man, where do I start?! This place is awesome. I saw Kaitlyn and she rescued my hair. She found the perfect hair color and cut that best suited me. I brought my 7 year old daughter for a cut and she loved it. They made her look and feel like a star. I highly recommend this place.
We love everything about Mazzaros! We buy all our coffee here, never miss hitting the wine room and the deli counter! Their pasta selection and olive oil selection are over the top!

Definitely my go-to store in Uptown, it's small and not always the cheapest for cupboard staples but as long as you're not looking for anything too exotic you'll find it at Langenstein's.  However, where they REALLY excel is prepared and local foods.  Making Jambalaya?  You'll find great quality ingredients at Langenstein's including outstanding Andouille, Tasso, mutlple options for par-boiled rice, etc. - or you can pick up a container to go for $4.95/lb.  Cheap?  Not necessarily.  Outrageously priced?  No.  Trust me, you'd be hard pressed to make most of their soups, gumbos, pastas, or anything prepared for much less at home - and then you'd have to have a great recipe as well as the skill and time to make it as good as Langenstein's.  It's easier for me to walk to Zara's but there is very little in that store that I really trust, it's about equidistant to shop at Whole Foods but there you just don't get the local selection or feel.

Langenstein's is a great shop to have in the neighborhood and even if I lived further away I would still come here for many items to cook with or even prepared foods.  It's definitely worth checking out.

September 27, 2016 - It has just come to my attention there have been major staff changes since I was at Molly's late June.  There is a new chef, Brandon Busby, who has worked at several 4-star Yelp reviewed restaurants and an positive article about him in Sauce Magazine Aug. 28, 2016.  It also appears new servers and other staff may also, have been replaced (YAY!).  

I sincerely hope this will make a huge positive change.  It would be great to see Molly's succeed.

Unfortunately, I have no chance to try again for myself.  I was visiting from out of town at the time.  I hope there will be no similar reason, like that one for my return to St. Louis, anytime soon(or ever).  But, those of you in St. Louis may want to check it out.

Late June 2016 - I was warned that certain dishes were inconsistent.  It was no better as we continued through our meal.

I ordered the Shrimp Po-Boy.  Supposedly NOLA style.  Not at all.

Been there and this was absolutely not what one expects from a NOLA Po-Boy.  To meet the NOLA standard the shrimp should have been deep fried with a spicy batter.  Not grilled without seasonings.  Cole Slaw (who is Cole anyway that a slaw was named in perpetuity) was seriously needed.

  Using a hard baguette made the whole sandwich difficult to enjoy because, it cut up my plete and caused the shrimp to squeeze out.  The six shrimp were blah.  No taste. The remoulade was fine.  Very little lettuce (caesar salad dressing) not slaw.

The brioche bun on the sizable burger which, a couple of PID enjoyed, would have improved the sandwich.

A PID ordered a cold shrimp cocktail which, came out AFTER all the HOT foods.

The curly fries were inconsistent.  Some were well cooked and others seemed to have been introduced too late to the fryer making them nearly raw.

A Partner-In-Dine ordered the Jambalaya.  Overcooked tough shrimp.  Boiled, bland sausages and slightly under cooked rice.  Very little flavor over all.

The new back room was fine.  The stairs dropping into the sunken room had NO rail and were rather steep.

More a bar than a restaurant destination.

My husband booked us a New Years couples massage. It was our first time trying this location and I'm glad he found it. We had a male and female masseuse and they were both great! We got back to our room a little late, but we were given our full hour for the massage. The atmosphere was excellent and the customer service was even better. We look forward to visiting again.

I love this place!  I moved here from Los Angeles where there is a ton of good sushi. It has taken me a long time and trying a lot of places to find one I really like.  This is the place!  It is a family business and they are very nice and I enjoy talking with them.  They pride themselves in having fresh fish and they are always coming up with new specialty dishes!

*I went here for the restaurant week upstairs* they had three burger choices and it came with a side of mac n cheese. The mac and cheese was really heavy and piled on with cheese. The burger was a weird combination because they stuffed it with salami. The other breakfast burger was just okay. For dessert, they had a fried Twinkie and I should have known better than to try it. The batter was not good and you couldn't taste the Twinkie inside. The staff was nice and the location is cool but I would have this as a lunch place. Go somewhere else for dinner

I've become a regular here.  It really does feel like a neighborhood place.  The guys who work here are super friendly and remember my usual order.

While they are friendly and talkative, they are just a little slow.  I think it's because they are doing such a good job & taking so much care with the food, but if I'm in a hurry I just make my order and come back to pick it up, or even call it in ahead.

Their bagels are good & I've enjoyed the Fresco veggie panini and tuna hoagie.  The quality of their food seems really fresh and good - i know they make a lot of stuff from scratch, including their soups that I keep meaning to try.
