I have never even left a review but felt the need to... we ordered nachos which were like concession stand nachos (if that) and $16... no cheese or toppings. That with two drinks for $40 was absurd. We didn't make it to a meal after that.

What a beautiful treat. Reminds me of Gladstones in Malibu but without the hustle and way better food. We lucked out getting seated right away at an indoor window seat. I could see why this would be really busy in summer. We'll definitely be back.

''I just wanted to drop you a line to say how impressed I am with the service from Sam at big brand tire in santa barbara location.This is the fourth time I've used your services in the last 10 months and today my son was tr for service and each time it's been so efficient my son was shock how great you guys are .I will definitely be using your service again and have already started recommending you to friends and family. Many thanks to Sam and all of the team for their help and honestly . Best in santa barbara

Very cute ice cream shop! Tons of flavors to choose from and not your normal Baskin Robbins flavors either! I had the egg nog and lemon with blueberries. Delicious and super creamy! Must stop by if you're in the Nashville area.

Flavors good, but extremely slow service when Restaurant was only 1/3 full on Thursday night. 

Actual meet VERY disappointing. Extremely overdone, but after 50 minutes didn't want to send it back.

This is a new bar restaurant in Hatboro. Hatboro really needs a hip location that can bring people out on the weekends. This may be the place! They have a really neat decor and it seems nicely planned and put together. We came around 8:00 on a Monday night and it was empty. They had a nice TV setup where we were sitting at the bar. The bar probably had over a dozen beer taps with an option for every micro brew fan! 

I love raw bars and they had fantastic oysters, albeit a little pricey. Their menu said they have a decent happy hour though!

Our calamari was tasty and seemed like it was homemade. (not the Costco bag that a lot of restaurants use) 

The only reason we give it 4 instead of 5 is price and the ultra pretentious jazz lounge music that was playing the entire time we were there. The music throws off the vibe of the place and is not fun. I do like that it wasn't too loud though either.

Inconsistent and VERY crowded. My second visit I ordered the chicken bacon avocado wrap to go. When I opened my nearly $11 wrap, it had chicken and avocado. No bacon, lettuce, tomato, or lemon aioli. Very disappointing for an almost $11 wrap. They also forgot my chips. But hey, at least I got a pickle right?

Going in here like buns heaven! Every buns and cakes here are delicious! I went in and have to get one of each. I gave only 4 stars because I tried to call several times during the special events to order cakes but the phone is NEVER pick up.
Great family owned restaurant!!! Best Italian cuisine in I have had! Love the atmosphere and great service!

Honestly I think I've missed something here. I chose Sun Sushi based on the percentage of 5 star ratings on Yelp. I called at 7:00 p.m. to make last minute reservations for 7:30 that evening, Friday. I was told by a women I spoke to that they were all filled and there was a line out the door. With that said, My friend and I thought to just just drive by and see for ourselves and or find another place to dine. We arrived at 7:30 no line and there were open seats at the sushi bar along with 3 empty tables... 

When we entered the restaurant the gentleman asked if we had a reservation and I told I called and the women that answered would take one. Anyway, We were seated. Service was very OK. It took me to finally get the attention of a server to take out drink and food order.

We ordered the Soft Shell Crab Tempura Appetizer, Salmon Skin Roll, Yellow Tail, Uni, Salmon, Sweet Shrimp, Smelt Egg with Quail Eggs and Halibut Sushi along with a Salmon-6-Step.

All the fish was of OK quality not the best. the Yellow Tail smelt a little fishy. The Smelt Egg presentation was sloppy with eggs falling off and the Quail Eggs about to drip off. The Salmon-6-Steps was very OK too. The Uni was not the price listed on the menu in fact it was an outrages $15 (isn't Santa Barbara famous for their Uni?) The worse part of the meal was the Tempura Crab and Fried Shrimp Heads. I don't know where they get the recipe from but it certainly was not Tempura which should be served HOT in temperature and light in batter. The coating was a very heavy batter and all the fried food was barely room temperature.. so bad was the Crab that I had to pick off the batter to eat the crab. 

Food OK, Tempura horrible, Service OK.

I moved in June. I called waste management to cancel my service, and they told me it  was canceled. I recieved a bill through the month of June and paid it thinking it was the last bill. I then recieved another bill for July. I called in August to cancel again telling the customer service representative that I had canceled in May. This representative told me that it was now canceled as of June 1. I received another bill in September, and called again. I was given the same spiel. I then got another bill in October. I called again, and told them how I canceled in May, August, & September. I asked for an official letter canceling my service. I did not recieve this letter, and instead got an automated call telling me I owed them money for this address. I again called waste management to cancel, and request a letter that explicitly canceled the service. I finally got a letter in November telling me that they cancelled the service because repeated attempts to collect the money I owed for this address had failed, and if I did not pay I would face the bill going on my credit. My wife called, and they told her that they would refund me. Why the hell wouln't they cancel my service when I called the first five time, and why do I still have to pay them for service that I canceled five times, and did not recieve at an address I do not live at. I HATE WASTE MANAGEMENT, I WISH THEY DID NOT HAVE A MONOPOLY ON GARBAGE SERVICES WHERE I LIVE OR I WOULD CANCEL THEM. THEY WOULD PROBABLY STILL BILL ME ANYWAYS!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

Came into town on business and flopped on my hotel room bed, exhausted, and desperately seeking comfort. 

Given my need for comfort, I immediately thought of pasta because it is INDEED comforting. Specifically fiocchi di pera. As a result, I searched everywhere for a restaurant that delivered and had pear pasta. Enter Bella's.

Bella's has a unique take on pear pasta called the pera satchel. It's fiocchi filled with pear obviously but topped with peas and prosciutto. Admittedly I was hesitant to order this as all the ingredients overwhelmed me, but it's honestly probably one of the better ones of this dish I've had.

Also, can we talk about their huge portions? Typically fiocchi is served as a dozen purses of pasta, but after ceasing my eating, I had eighteen left for the next day. Yes, folks, eighteen! I am still flabbergasted to this day.

And to top it off, in typical fashion, I went overboard and ordered bread and dessert. The bread was probably the one thing I didn't enjoy as I found it bland, but the dessert was godly. The Vesuvio, or their take on molten lava cake, is extremely rich and unless you've got a major sweet tooth, prepare for leftovers of that and the accompanying vanilla ice cream.

Needless to say, I think the only reason I didn't end up in food coma was because I managed to stop eating. So sheer willpower! That and I had work early the next day and was just grateful to have food and not bother hunting in downtown Tampa with the subpar weather we've been having. Anyway, this was just my experience with Uber Eats. I'd love to try the actual restaurant next time I'm in town.
2 words....Nick's Special.... best sandwich in philly hands down! Sarcone's hoagie roll. filet mignon. sauteed spinach. provolone. see about it!

First let me say that the salad bar was great 
Then it went downhill from there!
The order took forever and when I asked my server where it was she had a major problem !
Ask for the manager..never came to the table
We won't be back

We used to take our dog here for daycare a lot when we lived on this side of town, but were told she can't come back unless I call ahead and make sure there are enough dogs because she's too big for the small dogs and not big enough for medium. I was annoyed that this was their only response so stopped going for a while, but our usual boarding location was full one weekend so we took her here for boarding. They seem to take good care of the dogs, but the folks answering the phones and handling the reservations seem fairly absent-minded. I asked for 3 nights of boarding and to let her play with other dogs for the 2 days she was there. They had my old address so we updated that on the phone. When I picked her up, I was told she got a private play session (and nobody appeared to know if she even had her temperament test re-done like they promised when I dropped her off) so she never got to socialize while she was there -- again, like I asked for. And they *still* had my old address and contact information, so I guess it's a good thing they didn't need anything while I was gone. Seem like good people, but just absent minded I suppose. All in all, I wasn't impressed with the experience.

We loved their service! Everyone was friendly and the wait was less than five minutes. We love coming here for Taco Tuesday and  never had a bad experience. The manager even topped off our queso and chips for us. Great visit.

Came in while walking around State st and needed a treat! I got the crepe with banana and Nutella. It was pretty good! I loved that the crepe had parts that were crispy! I originally wanted banana and strawberry but that one is much bigger. It would be nice to have standard size with a small amount of banana and strawberries. Overall it was delicious!

I would like to give this restaurant four stars because the food was very good - it was light but filling and everything was very tasty. We especially liked the calamari appetizer and gyro my husband ordered. 
However the service was quite a miss. The hostess who sat us literally did not look at us. She just walked us to a table and pointed and said "Here" and then walked away to talk to some friends, it seemed. So our first impression was not great. 
Our server was really friendly and nice but very slow. We hardly had our water refilled once and after we paid for the check we waited over 15 minutes to get our card back. It was really strange and we left agreeing that the food was good but we probably wouldn't come back for a dinner when they might be busy.

Came here on a friend's recommendation and I was a little nervous because although we both like Indian food we have different taste in cuisine otherwise! 

Well, I can say my friend's rec was a good one! My friend had noticed in his previous visits that both Indians and non-Indians alike would come to this restaurant. I take this as a good sign as this usually means you can customize the heat level to your liking and that the dishes are, for the most part, not too strong in any one flavor. The restaurant is quite, cozy? There are maybe 9 tables all decently close to each other. The food makes up for whatever is missing in ambience!

We started with a free Mango Lassi (thanks, Yelp)! We also ordered the Butter Chicken (medium) and the Vegetable Jalfreezi (spicy). The dishes come with rice but we also got garlic naan.. I liked both dishes a lot, I found my friend's vegetable dish to be quite hot so if you don't enjoy spicy food maybe stick to the mild. My ideal spicy level is around a 6 so the medium was perfect for me! 

The portions were quite large, we both ended up having leftovers and the food came out quickly and was hot. We saw a couple waiters carrying sizzlers, I definitely want to try that on my next visit. The service was good, very prompt. I think this is a great place to stop by if you need a quick bite.

Overall, I enjoyed this place a lot and I would come back here again with family or friends.
Bring your appetite to this food truck! I have loved everything from Gigi's and is they are one of our go to food trucks. The carne asada fries were great, and steak and shrimp burrito is excellent.

I hate to even give them one star! Had the rear shock on my car replaced in the beginning of the year in 2011. Then took the car back for inspection in the beginning of October 2011 and was given a slew of items that need to be fix in order to pass. The shock was one of the them. I pointed out that it was done by NTB not long ago and the manager agreed to replace it at no cost to me for parts but will cost me labor. Which was OK EXCEPT I was not told that the after market part was used until the shock went AGAIN 5 months later! Took the car to other shop, mechanics that two separate locations made the same comments "looks like they used the after market parts or didn't even replace it at all!" Called the store, as i expected - NO ONE CARES! Good, I will take my business else where from now on. And btw, don't bite into the bait that some of the NTB mechanics will offer doing the work for half of the labor (off the books) and you only pay for parts. Not worth it since they don't guarantee their work. Very shady and sub-par mechanics! NEVER AGAIN!
I've always received the best service and their deliveries are always prompt and in less time that they state.  The veggie pizza is my favorite and it's great.

I ate dinner at 20 Manning this past Saturday night (Thanksgiving weekend) at 7:30 PM with my wife, sister-in-law and brother-in-law.  It was crowded when we arrived but we only had to wait a couple minutes for our table.  Our table was in a nook at the front of the restaurant by the window which was nice since it was out of the way.  The remainder of the space toward the back looked a bit cramped, so try to get a seat by the front window.  

Our waiter was attentive and knowledgeable although his attempts to up-sell on a couple items was pretty apparent.  I appreciated how he filled our water glasses up and left a full bottle of water on the table for us to re-fill at our leisure.  I wish more restaurants would do this.  

The beer selection both bottled and on tab was more than adequate and favored just slightly the craft beer category.  I liked how they had both a craft porter and craft stoudt on tap - in fact, the chocolate pumpkin porter was excellent.  We ordered the  pork pot stickers and deviled eggs for appetizers.  I enjoyed the pot stickers (4 of them); however, the deviled eggs were average at best, and frankly, lacking in flavor, which was disappointing as I was looking forward to them.  It's the only restaurant where I've seen deviled eggs on the menu, so I thought, incorrectly as it turned out, that they must be phenomenal if they're on the menu.  

No matter, as the Fish Tacos that I ordered as my entree (2 for $14) turned out to be the star of the night.  The tacos were on the larger side with plenty of the filling and I thought the guacamole that accompanied them was excellent.  

For dessert, we ordered the Bubbi's Apple Cake and the half-baked Toll-House cookie.  The cookie was mouth-watering and topped with a scoop of vanilla ice cream - I'd order this again.  I thought the Bubbi's Apple Cake, while generous in portion, didn't really even compare to some of the same apple cakes I've purchased at grocery stores which I have found superior.

Someone else in my party ordered the bison burger.  While I did not try it, he remarked that it was the best hamburger he's ever eaten - very lean but still juicy.  Sounds like the bison burger is another good menu option.

All in all, I'd give it a 3.5 stars - didn't blow my mind but I thought it was a good meal with reasonable prices.

Johnny Jinx was amazing! He is professional and personable and his was able to work with my random images to make an amazing semi realistic color piece for me with a reasonable price. I will go back again for my next tattoo.

I started going to Lynn 5 years ago when I lived in Soulard and I could walk to her shop. I'm very petite and don't have the patience to learn how to do my own alterations so I tend to see Lynn multiple times a year and have brought her all kinds of things - pants to hem and take in, suit jackets, skirts, multiple bridesmaid dresses, you name it. I can't walk to her store anymore, but she's well worth the drive and always does an amazing job!

Love this course!!  We play here quiet often and the staff is always super friendly and the course is well maintained and properly managed.  This course is not too hard but not too easy as it is pretty open but if you hit into the sage brush you most likely will not find it.  The green fees are in line with the course and everything it has to offer.

If you want to live around dirty people and crime then ... welcome to Foxwood Apartments ! If The smell of weed and cat piss doesn't bother you .. the kids breaking windows and fighting .. police activity .. this is your place to live ! Since this new management company took over, this place turned into the dumps . All the good people are moving out , and the section 8 is coming in !

I really want to love this place.... but I swear, the entree always disappoints! And for a pricier dinner... you need to have on point entrees! 

Great ambiance. Pretty good service. Sorta feels like the server has 1 too many tables to give great service. 

Apps are amazing! Oysters, calamari, gator hushpuppies, grit cakes... Love the local brewed beer. Desserts.... especially ice cream - YUM. 

You can't beat the patio and outdoor seating while the sunsets and you are waiting for a table.

I have eaten at Culvers in Wisconsin numerous times and have to say the Culvers in Tucson is not of the same caliber as the Midwest Culvers.  It seemed very disorganized or something.  It was the main supper hour (5:30 pm) and we ordered the 2 pc. chicken dinners and was told there would be a 15 minute wait.  We then re-ordered a deluxe butterburger combo and a salad for me.  My husband said  the burger was okay but tasted strange. (?)  My salad (which I loved up in Wisconsin) had warm, wilted, large chunks of lettuce, soft bacon, some cherry tomatoes and flecks of bleu cheese.  The so-called grilled chicken was lukewarm and tough.  We then ordered 2 cones and I think because we are senior citizens they figured we only deserved a kiddy-size cone.  The whole meal and general atmosphere at the restaurant was disappointing.  I will be waiting until I get back to Wisconsin this summer, to go to Culver's again.  Sure won't go to the Tucson one.  They may want to send their managers/trainers to the Minocqua Culvers to see how they need to train their employees to wait on people and mostly to cook.  I see the menu's are the same, but that's about it.  Very disappointing.

Dinner with the family. The wait was supposed to be 50 mins. It was actually a hour and fifteen min, we ended up pushing two tables together in the bar area. Our table was actually ready five minutes after we did that, but we were ready to eat so we stayed where we were. The server Jennifer was very nice and promptly put in our appetizer order before she even took our drink orders. The food was all delicious everyone enjoyed their meal.

I attempted a visit with some friends post-birthday dinner at Beau Monde a few years ago.  It was a weekend, it was sweaty and crowded...and not in a good way.  It reminded me of a slightly more upscale fraternity party with not the most amazing music and overpriced drinks.  I won't be returning for any dance nights.
The best banana pudding I've ever tasted, now that I'm back in Michigan I'm super bummed that I can't have more! So glad I tried it.

I kind of consider myself to be a burger fanatic. Maybe even a burger expert. I will go out of my way for a good burger.

I was invited to Ozona blue with some friends of mine. I was really hungry and decided to order... You guessed it... A burger.

And all of my travels throughout the United States and other countries I've never had a burger this good. I'm not kidding. I didn't see it coming. Completely shocked.

Get a burger. Let me see if I can be clear about this... When you go to this restaurant... Get a burger.  I wish I had taken a photograph of it but I was too darn hungry. It's huge... Massive... Deliciousness. 

Next time I go I will take a picture

Extremely disappointed. I had high hopes for this place and was looking forward to the baked Alaska. First we were put in a quiet, white, very uninviting room in the front. While the back room sounded lively and fun. Ordered the gulf fish topped with crab and side of potatoes. The entree/side tasted good, nothing special, but for $47 you expect more for fine dining.  Now for the long awaited baked Alaska that you see being flambéd in front of you on social media, not the case. Was given to us, cut up and put on our plates. On top of it the waitress complained that she hates when people try to take it home, which we did, because it's the size of a football and costs $19. And when she put it in the to go box, she only gave us half of what was left on the plate.
I like to make my own pizza at home with some Italian bread.  My friend told me I can get a fresh Cheese from Claudio's SO i tryed. Wow fresh cheese does make a difference.

Great for lunch and breakfast they have all the staples for lunch. They have good chicken salads, good Cuban sandwiches and the meals are generous portion sizes so you're not going to be starving after you finish. Convenient, great service and simple but consistently good food make this place a great part of this office community.

These guys are truly awesome!!! We stopped by their store in Reno last week just to look around and inquire about SUP's. Both of them were so pleasant to us, they spent a lot of time answering every question we had with no sales pressure at all to make a purchase that day. I didn't want to buy a Paddleboard at a place such as Costco or online and then not be satisfied with it a few months later. We ended up going ahead and purchasing the Sunset Cruiser, and the Blue Betty board which are truly beautiful boards and will last us a long time! Kudos to companies that have people that take the time to talk to people and show that they truly care about their customers!

Cool bar on the 11th floor of the Pontchartrain Hotel. Loved the view and atmosphere. Drinks were good too. Waitress should have offered the various Gins they had (which I didn't see until after I had ordered my gin & soda)

Great shop on State Street in the heart of Santa Barbara. Castle Roasters coffee and espresso. Yummy baked goods. Good teas and plenty of coffee merchandise. 

Come in and enjoy a great cup of crafted coffee and sit back and work or watch the world go by. Some outside seating. Get a pour over and relax.

What a difference a second attempt makes. Let's start with the service, a different crew was in tonight and service was outstanding, attentive but not over bearing, making sure all my needs were met.
The food was also better I felt; tonight there only was one sushi chef and the dynamite roll was amazing, so was the concord pike roll and the spicy yellowtail hand roll. The surprise was an amazing green tea ice cream tempura. Whatever the first experience was, it does not seem representative of the best Takumi has to offer.

I just wasn't impressed. 
A few friends of mine and I decided to check out the new restaurant on Mass Ave. Sunday afternoon/ early evening and there were very few people. Maybe it's just because their new.
We sat checked out the menu and decided to skip food. Nothing looked THAT good. At least not for the price. I will say though that what I saw brought out to other tables looked much better than expected. 
So, we settled on just doing drinks. I had a beer. They have a pretty good beer list. A friend of mine tried to get their signature drink but they were out of one of the ingredients. 
Overall the service was sloppy. The Bartending was slow given how few people were there. I'm sure I'll eventually go again once they work the kinks out but I'm in no rush.
Though long overdue, the recent renovation makes this a great coffee shop with a variety of indoor seating options to satisfy all. Also excellent outdoor area.  As always, the coffee is the best.
This place is within walking distance of my house, but I really like their food. Fried stuff is always crispy. The duck is my favorite

The food is decent, pretty much on par with Qdoba, Moe's, Chipotle, etc.  The queso is delicious, but pretty expensive at a $1.50 upcharge and I think I like Qdoba's better.

Extra star because the worker took a few extra seconds to properly wrap my burrito.  Nothing more infuriating than blowholes or loose shells - this was seriously the most expertly wrapped burrito I've ever received. Well done.

It's a Starbucks. Looks like a Starbucks. Lines like a Starbucks. Coffee tasted like Starbucks. Neither better or worse than any other! Conveniently located near to the worst DMV I've ever been to. Cannot be more glad that I got coffee here before my 5 HOUR WAIT at the DMV. Going to the DMV for you TN license? Go to this Starbucks first. Trust me.
Didn't stay to partake of anything on their menu-service was terrible with a F- you attitude and prices for domestic bottled beer were outrageous $6 for Miller lite. Won't be back.

This place charges for refills on Lemonade ,who does that?.
I had the halibut it was tough.

Words that come to my mind after my Kava at Sol. Relaxing. Healthy. New friends. The best Kavatender (service) anywhere in Reno! I could go on and on but you need to try it for yourself. I promise it's worth a trip to Sol. It's the type of place you go and play a game over Kava or journal. Let the creative juices flow.

Decent customer service.  Considering it was the weekend before a holiday and they were packed at the register, it is nice to see customer service being offered inside and outside.  I had something specific I wanted so I was not there long.  However, while I was there I noticed several customers being given directions on how to quickly find what they were looking for and when I asked for advice I was given an honest opinion.  Very helpful.  Also, I noticed that they were very attentive in helping customers carry their purchase to their cars.

This place has a wide selection of all brands of everything you could think of.  They have a wonderful selection of hard to find beers.  I enjoy drinking Hobgoblin from Wychwood Brewery in England only a couple places serve it draft in the Tampa Bay area but I know that I if want to get some for home I can get it here.

If you are looking for your holiday needs in this regard give these guys a stop.  I am sure they can help you get whatever you need and if not their personality says  they can and will give you the best advice on where to obtain it.

Wouldn't recommend plays out of state football over the lightening and blues game. Was playing country music and I requested for the hockey game to have sound and she said no that its football night. She then went to the back and turned on the football game. I'll  chose to support another place that supports local teams ! I hope all the Floridians do the same !

This is one of those random spots you wouldn't believe existed, but is always packed! A random taco shop two blocks from the beach and near a batting cage for the fun of it? All the taco options here are great and the parking is so easy. Sit outside and enjoy your grub in the sun. I always try something new and my kid sticks to the basics. Plus prices are great for the quality of food. Check this out next time you want something close to East Beach!

Le premier soir ou je suis passée devant ce bar, il y avait un cover de 10$ pour voir des artistes ce soir là, et le soir suivant, il n'y avait pas de cover mais pas beaucoup de monde (lundi soir). Par contre, la place est très belle et grande, il y a un très large choix de bières effectivement, et les serveuses sont très souriantes.
Bref, je n'ai pas vu le d.b.a en mode ambiance mais je l'ai imaginé ambiancé et je pense que ça doit être très cool!

Server was slow, food took forever to get out waited 20 minutes on a Monday morning. Food is whatever. Go elsewhere this place isn't worth the hype at all. Also have heard the place is dirty inside wouldn't surprise me.

Favorite Philly cookie, and I've had as many as I can get my hands on. I love their chocolate chip walnut cookie most. It has a great dough to chip ratio, and I love the thick texture. We usually end up buying several at a time.
We don't live close enough to visit every week (sadness), so I've found that they freeze well if you do it fresh! Then I can have a cookie whenever I want!

I love this place. They have everything -- and I mean everything -- you'll ever need there. They have a huge full produce section. Usually, everything is crisp and fresh. If it's not, it will be heavily discounted. And when it's discounted, the food is still good so long as you use it within a day or two.

They have all the pantry items you can think of -- and nearly in a huge variety of brands and varieties of flavors. The fridge and freezer section are packed. If you lived in India for a long time and get homesick for something specific, you will very likely find exactly what you want here.  You  buy items for your home shrine, cooking utensils and even cricket gear!

There's a bakery that has great bread every day. Right now, the serve yourself deli is closed due to COVID-19, but they have amazing "homemade" pickle and halwa.

The prices are reasonable as well. Very often in Indy, grocery stores like this will have "exotic" high end prices.  Here, they are very reasonably priced. If you wanted, this could be your only grocery store.

I have several friends living in Mumbai. I "take them with me" shopping many times and show them what is on the aisles. They say it's well stocked and except for some "strange brands" (some brands made in the US for the desi market) it looks just like their own store.

I usually don't leave reviews but this place touched me in a special place! I wasn't into it at first but my ex girlfriend really made me a fan. After I came a few times I knew I'd be coming here for life. 
-K.C.

Wish I could give zero stars.  Multiple bad experiences that threatened the lives of my dogs.  1) A misdiagnosis of cancer when it was an easily cured infection.  They wanted to do surgery, but thankfully I went for a second opinion.  2) Letting a dog suffer with a reaction to sedation for over an hour during euthanasia.  And I mean this dog was whining, trying to get up, drooling and eyes wild.  I was yelling for help and having to call the front desk and no one came to help. 3) Turning a suffering dog away at 1 am because they are short staffed.

These are just the top 3 bad experiences.  I stopped going there for routine care, but in emergencies the next place is 30 minutes further.  Guess I need to refresh my dog first aid because you can't count on them in an emergency.

I've discovered food crack in the form of Cuban sandwiches and sweet plaintains.

TaTa's knows how to do a top sirloin and grilled onions sandwich - ginormous in size, the pork was succulently sweet, encased in a french baguette that was a nice blend of greasy and crunchy. 

Overwhelming yumminess in sandwich form, my friends.

The side order of sweet plaintains was well worth the $4 extra dollars - it was also ginormous, and fried to perfection.

One of my cohorts in the trip to TaTa's tried the soup (apparently it's the Cuban version of chicken noodle) and she said it was to die for. My other friend tried the #1, and seemed in food bliss heaven when we finished as well.

TaTa's is tiny, but we managed to snag a table right at lunch hour rush. There was only one server, so we had to wait a bit for drinks/refills/extra sauces, etc., but it wasn't obnoxious. Their prices were a bit high, but well worth it. 

TaTa's has definitely confirmed for me that Cuban folk know their food. I'm eternally grateful they're willing to share.
Far exceeded my expectations. Trimmed back my two large sycamore trees as well as my two palms. Very professional. Cleaned up after themselves and left my yard looking great. Highly recommend.

How does a fast casual joint wind up serving one of the best burgers in town? It's because they don't overthink it. Maybe they're onto something with the "fries as main, burger as side" ethos. Patties err on the side of thin, which means you've got a lot more crispy, carmelized surface area. The Maillard Reaction = flavor, and I'm glad BFC has that figured out. The buns, near as I can tell, are baked on-site and the toppings are damn good too. Simple. I'm into it.

The eponymous fries are served up with a variety of choices likely to make your head spin. I typically stick with the Laura-derived kind - a potato named Laura! Who knew? The skinny fries (shoestring, curly) tend to be VERY skinny, so unless you love potato chip levels of crispness, I'd opt for the more generous homestyle cuts. 

But sometimes crispy is what you're looking for, especially when you have a ton of sauces to choose from! There's a rotating menu of sauces and flavored salts that represents everything you could think of, from your classic ketchups to your more avant-garde remoulades. I've been meaning to experiment with the cinnamon sugar "salt" alongside the blueberry ketchup for a dessert French fry experience. 

There's also a rotating selection of beers on tap, plus still more canned beers to choose from if so inclined. I haven't tried the housemade sodas yet, but it's a quaint touch.

Sometimes the line gets backed up at lunchtime (there are only two registers and the open kitchen is pretty small), but I can't say I mind. But the seating is occasionally rough going, especially at their busier hours - some of the skinny artisanal wooden tables, particularly along the windows, are actually too small to host as many seats as they attempt (6 people are really supposed to sit here?) and they're not *completely* level. So when you've got multiple people trying to sit with trays of burgers and fries plus a pitcher and glasses of beer, sitting at some tables can be a hazardous venture indeed.

But if that's the worst we have to deal with? As long as they keep serving up these burgers, I'll count myself lucky.

I proposed to my fiancé here. Yes, Southern is that good.  When I moved to St. Louis two years ago, I came because my then-girlfriend and I wanted to try the famous ribs at Pappy's, but the line was too long. We instead went next door to Southern, where the reasonable wait belied the beatific smile with which we would depart their hot chicken experience. It isn't good--it's possibly the best Nashville hot chicken in the world. 

I know because my fiancé is obsessed with fried chicken: traditional southern, country, Korean, Taiwanese, broasted, you name it.  Inspired by our first Revelation at Southern, we made a weekend pilgrimage to Nashville in search of the source, to pay our respects to the masters. We had fried chicken five-out-of-six meals, including Hattie B's and, of course, where Nashville hot chicken all started, the original Prince's. We were impressed, our taste buds were delighted, but what really amazed us was that the chicken at Southern was better.  Like Rick Lewis had dueled banjos with the devil and emerged with his soul and the best hot chicken recipe between heaven and hell. 

We returned to St. Louis with an even greater appreciation for this gem glistening at our oily fingertips. Since then, every time my then-girlfriend-now-fiancé comes to visit, we have to stop at Southern for four or five pieces of the dark meat (hers "hot," mine "medium"), a couple sides and some Urban Chestnut or Four Hands brews.  When friends and relatives come through town, I take them here.  When colleagues come in on business, I send them here.  It has become our favorite restaurant.

So when it came time to ask this amazing woman if she would spend the rest of her life eating chicken with me, I knew we had to do it here. A few weeks before the date, I dropped a note on the restaurant website's contact form and Billy the manager got back to me the next day to set up a phone call, excited to be a part of this special day. Apparently, nobody had ever proposed at Southern before, but Billy was happy to help me realize my modest vision and even had some great suggestions which we incorporated into the surprise. Day-of, Billy and his staff were also extremely helpful dealing with champagne and plastic flute drop-off as well as hooking up my friend Ken (ring-bearer and master of ceremonies) and Allison (professional surprise engagement ninja photographer) with uniforms so that my then-girlfriend wouldn't suspect anything was out of the lip-smacking, finger-licking ordinary. 

The photos speak for themselves, but the surprise went off without a hitch, not least of all because of the enthusiasm, whimsy and professionalism of Southern's staff. After the champagne was quaffed and the applause subsided, they even gave us matching Southern t-shirts to help commemorate the day.

So thank you Billy and the entire staff at Southern for rolling out the red carpet, to Ken Mao at Ful (www.facebook.com/eatful, @eatful) for being the master of ceremonies and Allison Slater photography (allisonslaterphotography.com, @allisonslaterphotography) for the amazing pics. You all helped make this a day we'll never forget!

Such a breath of fresh air and a relief from the numbingly bad diners that we have here in Largo Clearwater. This place is excellent beautiful clean and the food is so well presented and so very good. Fresh ingredients friendly waitstaff outdoor dining and mimosas you can't beat it.
ARM replaced my engine...no complaints.  They do all of my car repairs: oil, lube, filter; brakes; tires; etc...great friendly staff.  Support a great LOCAL business.

Small restaurant but the pizza is fantastic. With locally sourced and fresh ingredients paired with the brick oven and thin crust New York style you really can't go wrong. The owner Tony is great as well this is a hidden gem in downtown highly recommend.

Booked this hotel last minute on the Hotel's Tonight App and was not disappointed. It was conveniently located in the heart of the French Quarter right behind Jackson Square. The room was small but modern. We didn't face Bourbon and so we didn't encounter any of the noise issues you would expect from a hotel in the quarter. The staff was extremely helpful and polite. And the 2 complimentary drinks we received upon arrival didn't hurt either.

The food was amazing. My husband had the French today and loved it, I had the chef strata, and my bday twin had scrambled eggs, bacon & the amazing hash browns. Seriously, the hash browns were the best. The beignets to start were amazing. It just always makes me sad that there is never a gluten free given option for our gluten free friends. The litter of mimosas were ok. The only thing lacking was the service, from the house to the server, it was lackluster to say the least.

We were a party of 12 that had reservations and we were seated right away.  Chris, our server, was great.  However it took two hours to get our meal.  Sides were cold, steaks not cooked to order and after much confusion we were finally told they were out of the wine we ordered. A member of our party talked to Mike Kelly twice.  Mike was very rude and offered no type of an apology.  We won't be back.

Sub...Hoagie...Po'Boy...Torpedo...Grinder -  no matter what you call it, there is an essential quality about these style sandwiches no matter who makes them or where you purchase them. They come on some sort of French bread  (or Italian, depending on your neighborhood.) Today's PSECS subs came on a crispy-crust, French baguette: crunchy on the exterior, and soft/chewy on the interior.

Fillings are up to the customer who can choose from a list of hot, cold, wrap, or salad preparations listed on the wall and on the on-line menu. We opted for two simple, straightforward subs we order almost anytime we are trying out a new venue or chain. Unfortunately, what we received did not resemble the subs pictured on their advertising. Of course, frequently that is the case and accompanied by the disclaimer, "serving suggestion." 

The fillings were sparse...really sparse; but they were fresh and flavorful.  Nonetheless, it was  disappointing to get nearly twice as much bread as filling. (Compare/contrast my photos with the menu photos the company provides.)

Fries were mixed in terms of quality: Cut Fresh, yes; Fried Nicely, yes...BUT other than the few 2" ones pictured on the photo I took and posted, they were little 1-inch pieces and smaller, hardly big enough to pinch between your fingers when trying to extract them from the cup-container. Flavor was good...at least from what we could tell with these nibbles.

The employees were friendly and courteous. The interior of the building, located in the corer of a strip mall, was dim and dingy (but appeared clean).

It's unlikely that we will return to this place again. But, as with nearly all my reviews, I urge you to check it out for yourself. Just ask them to be sure to stuff your sammie with a value congruent with what you order and how much you pay.

Ever had undercooked foie gras? Nasty (as in raw and gelatinous). I had it here. I'm still ill. An entirely underwhelming meal. Kurobata pork chop was lukewarm and greasy. Lamb was undercooked, too. Service was attentive and polite but the food was forgettable. Nothing to see here folks - just keep moving.
Water front table with a nice menu. Buffalo shrimp was too saucy for my taste but they were big and fresh! I had a gyro, it was huge and tasty.

I've been going here since 2016 and never realized how great the location is! The last time I went in with the Yelp team members and they absolutely loved it! The place is byob + byo food which is great considering it's located near some popping food joints! Def one of my go to places for hookah in town! Also, Shoutout to the servers here they are so attentive and personable! Also, they always check wether you want a coconut coal or easy coal which is a huge + because most of the other places don't have options!

If you're in need of amazing sushi, ramen or dumplings...OBON will deliver and then some. 

It's busy so be sure to get reservations, but you will not be sorry. I got the street noodles (which was the best meal at the table) my wife got an alternate tuna roll (no avocado due to allergies - but it was so so good) and our intern got the ramen...and it was all amazing. 

Going back soon...

I love this store and always visit it when I go to Cajun Kitchen -- they have Calpico liters in many flavors.  Produce is solid and they have a good variety of Asian foods -- Indian, Thai, Chinese, Vietnamese to name a few.

Willa's is the 2nd restaurant located in the heart of North Hyde Park directly across from Rome + Fig.  And although the restaurants are drastically different, it holds its own.

Willa's is a scratch kitchen and overall it's just good eating.  

We tried nearly everything on the menu...well about 60% of it, which is just plain greedy but the menu concept really makes it easy.  And there are plenty of options for vegetarians and carnivores.   

We had the oysters, prosciutto, pull apart bread, house salad with the green goddess vinaigrette, shrimp cocktail, braised greens, Mac & cheese, potatoes, broccolini, salmon, and chicken.  We also ordered the pickles and mushrooms but unfortunately they never showed up.  Based on the group's consensus, the stars of the show were the oysters, salad, greens, broccolini, Mac, and chicken; however,  you can't go wrong with any of the other items.

Check it out and keep an eye out for Willa's Provisions-- the sister Coffee/Tea/Pastry Cafe.  

.

Best sushi this side of the bridge! More than a roll bistro... All of the traditional yummies like Ikura, Uni, Ebi with heads and super fresh sashimi. Plus a fantastic appetizer menu. Will be my regular St Pete spot :-)

Food is still fab, although there seems to some questions regarding the mac and cheese.....hmmmm......! Still, the greens are a delight and the catfish was perfectly cooked. And talk about cornbread! Great crumb with just a hint of sweetness. Go back for something other than the M and C and see what you think!

If you're new to this vegetarian world like me and really really miss cheesesteaks and sandwiches this is def the place to go. Service was great, they guy working explained everything and gave great recommendations. Prices are fair and the food is good. I'll definitely be back.

We made reservations for a Saturday evening.  Glad we did. Barely two months open and this place is busy.  Mind you it is small, but that is part of the attraction.  We enjoyed 9 different dishes.  Sourcing is tops. Prep is tops. Presentation is tops.  Taste is over the top.  The menu has several unique offerings for the curious, so be curious and go for it.  Other reviews mentioned the high prices.  The price range begins at $6 and goes up. The higher prices are justified by the kitchen skills and the sourcing.  The portions are appropriate for what their mission is.  Higher prices are not always an affordable option, however, the offering equals the price at Camel's Crossing.  Awesome experience.  And the service, excellent, friendly, and sincere.

Spiritland Bistro is a gem tucked away just off the downtown area, since upscale vegan options are limited there.  This would be a great place to take friends with different food preferences, since the menu is friendly to diets, and well laid out.  

The food preparation was gourmet and service was very attentive even though the restaurant was busy.  There was also a good selection of organic and bio-dynamic wines from local vineyards.  I will definitely return.
Been going here for years, great employees, great atmosphere, never gotten a bad haircut here.

I haven't been here since the smoking ban...mainly b/c the smoke was out of control.  Even though I've  requested the non-smoking section each visit, the smoke smell would just seep over, which is why I give it 3 stars.  The food is cheap and decent, but the smoking was just out of control, and led me to stop eating there.  Perhaps the rating will go up once I check it out...without the smoke.
Love this restaurant! Super flavorful and affordable....just be careful because spicy means spicy!!
Friendly relaxed atmosphere. Very good coffee and beverages. Extremely tasty pastries, but cannot give it a full 5 stars because the egg casserole and taco bowls are just okay.

As a customer for years, I can vouch for the great service and extreme satisfaction. Chris A's attention to my changing locks keep me coming back for more. Their nail services are clean and efficient by really attentive staff. You can't go wrong at this salon.

Best pizza in Manayunk roxborough area!

Food is delicious the girls at the counter are a little slow but the food makes up for all of that.

Thank you Mr.p!

We loved everything about this restaurant for dinner! The restaurant had an amazing atmosphere, the jazz band was beautiful, our food was delicious and our server Santoya pulled all of those things together to make a perfect last night for my birthday weekend in Nashville.

I went here with a friend to get a quick bite, however, from the read of the signage I thought it would be someplace where we could get a quick glass of wine and "aperitivi" type foods (the signage does say "Tapas", so....).  When we entered, I realized that it was more of a "cafe'" and having seen the menu and its hours, it is more of a breakfast/lunch/late lunch spot.  It is a welcome surprise to this shopping area since there aren't really any "easy" places to go and have a quick piece of cake and coffee or a sandwich.
The people who work there are nice enough and quite attentive.  The food is solid and again, it is an easy, home made quality kind of spot.  NOT fancy and not hip, just simple.

Having thought it was one thing and instead another wasn't a bad thing...but just so any of you who may read that awning thinking "Tapas" means what I thought it did...it doesn't :-) But, if you are looking for a quick and easy something as you shop until you drop at Mayfield Common, this is a reasonable spot to consider :-)

Very much recommend these guys! We called them somewhat last minute (only about two weeks in advance) and they provided us a fair quote and time they would arrive. We moved about two years ago with a similar size space and it took three guys 6 hours to move it all. These guys ran, no like they literally ran to and from the truck. They loaded and unloaded everything in 2.5 hrs. Huge deal when they other guys took 6. They were professional, tidy, and took good care of our things. Would book them again if we need to move!

I feel so blessed to of found Top Cat & Tails! They both did such a amazing job with my little huy! He is a long haired Minuet and had never been groomed before! They took their time and really loved on him and made him and myself feel very comfortable and the results were fantastic!! We will definitely be going back for monthly maintenance!! Thank you both for taking such good care of my sweet little man! He looks beautiful!

Yay they deliver!  

Staff is personable and go out of their way to help you out.

Food is exactly what you'd expect and the pad thai is delish.

Tip:  They are light-handed with the hot/spicy seasonings...so if you like it hot, get it realllly hot

I got the home skillet with scrambled eggs and a side of toast. The potatoes and veggies in the skillet seemed more like frozen recooked  OBrien then home cut and fresh. The scrambled eggs weren't fluffy at all:(  A few of us got scrambled eggs and they all were cooked the same. Not whisked and on low heat and fluffed. They were flat looking and not mixed well because you could see the whites still in the scramble. The place itself was quaint and cute with a diner feel. I would give this place a second shot but they gotta nail the basic scrambled eggs first. The front lady hostess was friendly and they had a young boy (maybe 12?) who sat us. He was sweet and attentive. 5 stars for the boy just for being a super helper :) probably helping out the family and he was a trooper and smiled while doing it.

I don't think it is just me. Not worth the price. I had Carmelita's Chicken on 9/18/2011. Very little chicken. The Rigatoni was nowhere near cooked.  I forget what my wife had, but it too was not worth it and her bow tie noodles were not cooked as one would expect.

Story highlights because this one is long: "Her dress was not good taste." "Your dress looks better than that other bride." "You stand too comfortable. You should suck in more." "You're going to fall on your face at your reception." "You're a waste of my time."

I went to Elegant Alterations yesterday to get an estimate on alterations to my wedding gown. The dress itself was just under $4000. With that in mind, I wanted the alterations to be done well, but also still be affordable since I spent most of my budget on the dress itself. I told Cathy beforehand on the phone that I wanted an estimate on my dress alterations, and she said to come by anytime after 4:45. I show up at 5 because I had trouble finding the place, and she is passive aggressive to me about being late. I just shake it off because she's right, I was later. Next, she tells me to put on the dress. When I come out, she starts comparing my dress to the girl who had been there when I came in (who I knew from college, but hadn't mentioned that yet) and saying mine was better and hers was ugly with no taste. I tell her that both are great, just different! I said her dress fits her personality well and she seemed to like it. She rolls her eyes.

Next, when she is pinning my dress, she tells me she needs to hem the back part of the underlining, and I tell her that isn't necessary because I am on a budget, and that part won't matter for how I have my reception planned. She continues to try to bully me into hemming the dress her way by saying, "when you fall on your face at your reception, you'll think of me and know I was right." Still I don't budge. 

Next, when I'm standing waiting for her to get something, she tells me I'm "standing too comfortable" and motions to my stomach sticking out. She goes on to tell me that I need to suck my stomach in all day on my wedding day because it's worth it on a special day. Cute.

She also quotes me on $35 per bustle, and insists there needs to be 3, which I now see from other past reviews that she was charging me $15 more than other people. At this point, I think she realizes that I don't have endless money to burn because I keep insisting on budget-friendly alterations due to the dress already fitting me so well (it fits like a frickin glove, it just needs a hem and bustle). Because she sees I have a price limit, she starts getting more aggressive and dismissive with my feedback and reminding me of all the more wealthy people she's done dresses for *name drops specific Beaman family members(who I also know and went to college with so that was uncomfortable again)*. 

At this point, I've been there over an hour (15 min of which she spent talking about other people's gowns and personal lives that I quite frankly don't care about at all and it's not my business who got a divorce), so I say I need to go and I'll compare prices elsewhere and get back to her. She freezes and acts surprised that I'm taking n my dresses with me. I remind her that I told her on the phone that I was just getting a price estimate, and she responds by saying "lots of brides call me, that's not my fault." Got a pen? Write it down. That's what our appointment was for, and I was clear about that. 

Next, she starts berating me about how I had "wasted her time" and she kept repeating "MY time is money." I say, "I'm sorry if there was a misunderstanding, but I was clear on the phone about what I wanted." So she starts trying to bully me (again) into leaving my dress there, saying all her pins and markings are already on my dress, and her pins "are her money." I tell her I'm sorry she feels that way, but I'm taking my dress with me, and pick out the closest pins to me and reach to hand them to her. She doesn't even look at me and gestures for me to put them in the container at her feet. I genuinely didn't understand so I said, "do you want these back?" And she nudges the container at her feet towards me, while I'm still in my fitted gown and covered in open pins. So I scrunch down, put them in the container and go change. When I come out, she tells me to hang up the dress so she can check for any more pins, and begins angrily erasing the markings she made with a wet rag. She does this for a long time in silence and very aggressively on my dress to make a show of how inconvenient I was to her, and I just stood there in silence and watched. I won't apologize for something I didn't do wrong and isn't my fault. I was clear on the phone, and she had been disorganized, rude, shamed my body, and talked crap about other women that weren't there to defend themselves. 

I respect strong women, especially business owners. However, I will not give my business to anyone who body-shames women, gossips to strangers about private business, bullies to get their way, is elitist about their clientele, or is just overall unkind. Oh. And she quoted me $350 for a small hem in the front, and a bustle. You're cancelled, Cathy.

You MUST try the chicken soup when they have it.   (But leave some for me please) Amazingly delicious along with the other soups and yummy food.  So happy to have this place down the street from my house.  The Nutella chocolate cake is also addictive as per my daughter (she doesn't share when it comes to this cake). Just go check this place out, you won't regret it.

Decided to give this place a whirl after someone recommended it to me. I'll never take their advice again. This restaurant was still serving food and drinks all while have NO running water! I know restaurants have been struggling through the pandemic, but safety doesn't take a holiday. How were they washing glasses, utensils or their hands?! The server informed me they were using hand sanitizer, as if that were supposed to make me feel better? Will not be coming back here again, not after these shenanigans.

A disappointing visit. Yes, it was a Saturday 6:15 reservation, and yes, it was fairly crowded, and we were a table of seven.  
We got our rather simple drinks 40 minutes after being seated. My Belvedere martini was essentially water - it had either sat for too long or been shaken 20 times. 
The calamari was fine, nice and crisp, if not terribly hot. 
Our dinners were served after 8:00. My Caesar salad was soggy and flavorless.  The Fantasia Di Mares:  served over very al dente pasta, the unseasoned fresh seafood was tasteless, as were the red or white "sauces" that had been poured over them.  There was certainly no temptation to dredge your bread to capture the flavors. 
The New York strip itself was praised as very good. It is listed as being served with steak fries. Our diner requested those be replaced with mashed instead, for which we were charged an additional $8.   
Our two vegetarians enjoyed their Buffalo Napoleons.
This visit was apparently a lesson not to eat out large on a Saturday night. We've enjoyed this restaurant for 20 years as a "treat". Like most diners, we assumed Aldo's could handle their expansion. Oh well
 I must add that the sommelier was wonderful, advising us on a marvelous wine when our requested was out of stock. 
So good we had two bottles, happily, and in good company. With a new understanding that even CaffeAldo can't necessarily handle a Saturday night crowd.

Pizza Reno was okay. It is nice that they have dedicated parking on the side of their building. The service was okay. The food was good, not sure if I would go out of my way to eat there again but would definitely stop in if I was in the area.

First of all I love Starbucks. My husband and I were looking for coffee the day we left Reno. We figured any Starbucks is the same. I was disappointed with this location and had to wait over 25 minutes  for two coffees!   The way it was set up it was awkward to say the least. It seemed we had to push chairs out of the way to walk out....the one and only door we had to enter. The workers were friendly enough but it just seem to take forever and was awkward.

I went here for a first date last weekend.  We did not have a reservation, however we didn't arrive until 8:45 or 9pm so I think we must have missed the dinner rush.  We were sat in a corner to ourselves, which was nice to be able to hear each other.  There weren't a ton of people there but I thought it was a little noisy for the number of people.  I ordered the scallops which were fantastic!  My date ordered the filet, which he enjoyed as well.  The service was not very memorable.   They left us alone enough to talk but I never felt that I need to get their attention either.

The service was very good and our food came out pretty quickly. The food was just so-so though. My grain salad (Farro?) has crunchy bits like it was undercooked or left out to harden. My husband has the chicken and said it was dry. Honestly not a terrible meal, but at $17 a plate it was not worth the price.

I did not read the reviews before I purchased the groupon and took my child there. With that being said the place was clean. We thoroughly enjoyed the open play. My experience with the staff was limited, they didn't seem overly friendly but they were not offensive. However, my mother was watching my son and was looking for something fun to do with him. She arrives, during open play, and the male employee at the counter was completely rude to her, to quote, "your daughter told you about the groupon but not the socks".   The other employee also was nasty to her. 

I am upset that such a clean well organized place that deals with children can employ people who are outright rude and unwelcoming. I will have to give serious thought if I will return again.
The Bahamian chowder and shrimp tacos were amazing! The margarita flight is a must try!
Amazing people who did a fantastic job!  Thank you for squeezing me in!  Very affordable and very professional!

I dined at Uva last night with my family. We were celebrating my birthday.  This was our first time at Uva. I have heard great reviews from a couple of friends and wanted to try. I can't say enough about the experience.  We loved it!! Our dinners were outstanding. I had the Branzino which was expertly filletted tableside. My son had the lobster ravioli, husband had veal with shrimp and other son had pasta primavera. We all enjoyed appetizers or salads as well. The deserts are all homemade so make sure you don't miss out! I had tiramisu which was completely over the top delicious! We also sampled the bread pudding,mango sorbet and flourless chocolate torte. The staff at Uva is wonderful-all at the top of their game. The owner came by and offered us complimentary lemoncello.  : )  If my highlights on the culinary experience are not enough, dining at Uva and listening to the live entertainment will delight you as well. The vocalist working last night had a voice like Frank Sinatra or Tony Bennett!!  Several people were celebrating birthdays last night.  He honored each of them.  Unbelievable experience!!! I  wish I could give six stars!!
Egads, man! If you don't get the huevos rancheros, get the enfrijoladas. And douse your biscuit in their blueberry jam!

Pretty amazing. Best Vanilla iced latte ice had in awhile. They sell the Odwalla line of organic juices which are good. Food is pretty tasty as well. 

Bathroom was a bit dark, would have liked it better lit. Other than that, was pretty nice spot.

The best massage I've ever had!! Went with my boyfriend for a couples massage and both the women we had had did an amazing job. The atmosphere is calming and very welcoming. Their last at the front desk are very accommodating and the massage therapist ask lots of questions and make sure to get those link areas out. This was my boyfriends first massage and he's hooked. If you're looking for a day of relaxation, this is the place to be!

had lucky lunch at luke's, at the bar. ended being a great experience, shuck-el man was fun to watch and to talk to, good gumbo, plum oysters, but the best.....rabbit liver pate and the rest was also good

Pros: 24 hours entry, new equipment, dumbbells up to 150lbs, and plenty of parking. 

Cons: 
-Waaaay too overcrowded at peak times. I'm not one to take group classes, but the rooms always seem overpacked with people 
-The place is run by children. They're all very young, and professionalism is minimal at best. I don't even scan in when I go because nobody is paying attention, and I am rarely greeted upon entry. Usually the kids are huddled around joking with one another, playing on their cell phones, or playing on the computer. 
-Next to the gym is a pizza place, a donut shop, etc. I worry that the temptation of the junk food is a lot to handle for some people, and I feel bad that they have to walk in/out of the gym with temptation surrounding them. 
-Not enough mirrors. The power racks are facing blank walls, so I can't watch my form effectively or efficiently. 
-High pressure sales for PT. Signing up for a membership was easy enough, but their PT salesmen are very aggressive. I went in for an assessment, and it was nothing more than an hour-long sales pitch. I wasn't impressed with the training staff. I'd watch them take people through sessions while I did cardio, and it seemed like everyone was getting the same workouts: TRX squats, ball slams, and ropes. I'm not paying for that, and I pity anyone who fell prey to their high-pressure sales tactics.

I cannot stress enough how lucky you will be if you get your hair cut by Teresa.  I have had Ouidad cuts,  and also Deva cuts in New York but none of these compare to the gorgeous styling I received by Teresa.  Can not recommend her highly enough for curly hair!!!

If you look at my reviews, I have eaten many places in NOLA. I love to find new places to eat. With that said how did I not try this place sooner? 
     First the ambiance and decor are very unusual and make you seem at home in the bayou. They have 3 sections of seating sort of shotgun style. While we were in there, they were playing some Cuban music. Although they will play anything with a good beat. The staff is super friendly and always check on you to make sure your OK. They will also recommend the best po boys if you unsure what you want. And they will make sure you get it the way you want. Spicy or not. 
     Now the GREAT part. The food. My son who is 11 is very picky. He had a plain cheeseburger po boy. His mind was blown. And having it look like a po boy made him feel he was eating a Cajun cheeseburger. Nice move. My wife who love Roast beef po boys and knows when she's had a good one was very impressed. She may have left a crumb but I doubt it. The meat was tender and full of beef flavor. It really didn't need and gravy but the gravy put it over the top. Just enough to make the bread soggy but not falling apart everywhere which is a BIG bonus. A meat eaters heaven for sure. Myself had a shrimp poboy DA YAT. Which is a shrimp po boy smothered in Gumbo!. Man let me tell you, I was in heaven. The shrimp had a light breading and very crisp which is a 10 in my book! A medium Cajun flavoring not heavy so you can taste the freshness of the shrimp. Dressed with mayo, lettuce no tomato and pickles. My daughter who can eat lava with a spoon had a shrimp po boy WHO DAT, which is a spicy version smothered in Etouffee sauce. Again you can taste the freshness of the shrimp but the etouffee sauce was magnificent. Not to thick and not to runny. Silky smooth sauce that complimented the po boy nicely. And then to top it off the owner let us try there praline ice cream. POOF!! Mind blown. The ice cream was very creamy and sweet just like you want it. 
     So in summation, I can't believe it took me so long to find this place. I would highly recommend this place to anyone that wants a GREAT po boy. By the way if you take a food tour. This is one of the stops on the tour. Great place and great food. Must try

We have loved belonging to the Nashville Boat Club!  The boats are always in like-new condition and never have issues reserving them.  The staff is great and very helpful.  Wish we'd joined sooner when our kids were younger.

We'll let's just say we all like to try new things and new places. We'll today was one of those I never been there days lol so I gave it try, and turns out it was not what I expected at all. It took me a while to even look through the menu and decide on what to try. It finally came down with me just letting the server know what I want lol It didn't take long for my food to come out at all but it could've also waited a little longer to come out as well. but any ways lol the food was very plain meaning no salt nor pepper nothing was flavorful lol the orange juice was great by the way. but seriously the sausages could've been cooked more the eggs was just cracked and cook with no salt or pepper added to it. the biscuits was very dry with no taste at all and the gravy was not gravy was what not what  I know gravy to be. P.s I tried it....

Originally from the area and had to try out the revamped Reading Terminal Market. It's a must go to for lunch, a fun afternoon of trying new foods or just being a straight out foodie for a day. The assorted venues offer a wide range of food options and fun trinkets.  We walked away stuffed from burgers and shakes from Hungry Burger, delicious coffee and a cute tote from the coffee shop, a great assortment of jams from the Amish shop, and the most amazing fudge and dark chocolate peanut butter cups from Meiler chocolates.   My older kids loved citing all the movies they could think of that were filmed here, I wish I'd googled that prior to heading there.  Took the train in to the city and  had a blast!

Don't have too much to say about this place that hasn't already been said.  The ambiance here is nice - similar to a bistro and great for a date night.  The service was just ok - not extremely coordinated. Even though there were only about 6 other occupied tables in the restaurant, our waiters weren't communicating and we had one waiter come and give us menus after we'd already ordered our entree selections from another waiter.  The food was nothing noteworthy.  For the prices, I honestly expected something more creative or authentic.  I think that is really the bottom line about this place - it is overpriced for what it is.  I imagine they are able to stay in business because there are several hotels in the vicinity that point unknowing tourists to this restaurant.  If you want an authentic Italian dinner and are willing to pay Valentino's prices, I would suggest going to Moto in the Gulch or Rolf and Daughters in Germantown.  Much better quality food and service for the price.

This place changed it's name or re-branded itself from the previous "Venito's"...

The slightly-deep-dish pizza here is pretty good, yo (albeit greasy).  They say they deliver super-late (4 AM?) if you're in the city.  The couple running this place is enthusiastic and accommodating.

The pizza is ridiculously inexpensive.  Personal pizzas are around $7 with a drink; a large two-topping for a friend and yourself is $7.99 (dine-in).  Clientele is mostly businessmen who know Venito's Secret.

It's a dive, but who cares.  They finally procured booths to fill the place and an awkwardly large, high-res, flat-screen TV on which the owners play torrented movies or whatnot.  I come here frequently.

Located in the terra incognita across from the YMCA on Church.

The people here were very friendly. Me and my boyfriend went in looking for a fish tank and the aquarium manager Bill came and helped us out. He helped us select the tank and all the other accessories we needed to go into our tank. The puppies they had were kept in clean cages and look very happy. They also had a very big selection of fish to choose from.

I was kinda excited to try this place- unfortunately I probably won't be returning. First off, the decor is totally confusing. The inside is dark, and they didn't try to do a 1950s theme at all. 

Food was nothing special either. I got a regular cheeseburger and it was mostly bun. Thin, bland patty. Cheese fries were good.

Menu was pretty extensive, maybe there's something they're better known for. Not sure if i'd return

I took my parents here for dinner last night and I have to say it wasn't one of the better dining out experiences I've had. Maybe my service expectations are higher because I'm a waitress but I really felt that the service was lacking. Our server was so cheeky it bordered on rudeness and she seemed unfazed when my mom sent back her salmon for being too rare. Even though I know it's not her fault that it wasn't cooked as my mom specified, it's your job as the server to take responsibility for the mistake and apologize. I have to say though that the manager overheard my mom's complaint and took care of it quickly and very efficiently, but still with some serious attitude problems. Overall, I was impressed with the beer list and enjoyed the tuna appetizer but was overall left underwhelmed.
Amazing food!  I had the pulled pork and my husband had the boneless chicken.  He had the bread pudding for dessert.  It is now one of my favorite places!

Overall, the food here is great. But I felt kind of deceived. Alma de Cuba means the Soul of Cuba, yet none of the food was really that Cuban (I took my Cuban boyfriend's family here and they would agree). If anything, it was a random mix of Hispanic and Latino food and if the thread between the menu items was just food from Spanish-speaking countries, then that is kind of painful. The interior was great and entertaining, and the service was phenomenal - truly a Starr restaurant. It's a little overpriced in my opinion, but still worth to try out. The drinks were the best part. The mojitos and caipirinhas were fire.
This is a great place to grab a quick bite for lunch. The Venezuelan Arepa was excellent. Passion fruit juice was really good too. Fries were just ok. Friendly staff.

Well sh*t, I honestly do not know where to start...

This place was INCREDIBLE. Everything from the drinks, to the service, to the food was top of the line. My gf and I went on our yearly visit to our college city Philadelphia for New Years...and boy we were in for a treat!

Drinks - upon arrival our table wasn't quite ready so we grabbed drinks at the bar. One of my favorite New York classics is a Paper Plane (equal parts bourbon, lemon juice, aperol, and amaro nonino) which the bartender made fantastically. Every Paper Plane comes out slightly different and I have to say his was one of my top 3 ever...

Service - freakin' impeccable...if only I could remember our servers name! (Black hair, tattoo sleeve, 30-40 year old lady) She was INCREDIBLE, and made us feel like we were in her own home. We never had to ask for water/more drinks, the table was always cleaned immediately after finishing each course and she even helped me out with some of her own personal tea (I had come down with a small cold while visiting so this was quite amazing!). She even had the chef change one of the courses because it contained fois gras which I am not a fan of because of how it is obtained. Unbelievable. 10 stars if I could!

Food - out of this world!!! Very unique and interesting flavors in every dish, especially in the scallop dish. The technique and mastery of each dish that came to our table was extraordinary.

All in all the experience was one of the best I have ever had anywhere in the world! I will be returning in a weeks time when I fly back for the Super Bowl! Go Birds! Cheers!
Fantastic soft shell tortillas and Mexican rice. The only thing wrong was that the shell was not warm. Everything else was great. The floors were clean, tables were clean and staff was friendly.

This is bar is located behind the Sampan restrurant - its a cool little hip place to start off the night for drinks. 

There is limited seating - only one long table and the bar area. It gets packed around 11ish so if your looking for a place to sit, good luck! 

The drinks are averagely priced and their scorpioan bowls are very popular.

DO NOT GO HERE FOR THE FOOD!!!!!

Shallo's has your typical deep-fried bar food.  Their home-made chips are great, but that's about it.  

GO HERE FOR THE BEER!!!

You want variety?  They have it!  The boast over 500 different beers throughout the year.  Included in that is domestic junk, but you still can get just about anything you can dream of here.  It's a very crowded, cramped place and can get very loud during the weekends.  The service is often slow, but that's what you get when you go to a bar to eat.  This is not a good family restaurant, nor a good place to take a date (unless you and that date just want to get plastered).  It is also very pricey.  However, anyplace that has Arrogant Bastard on tap will get my approval.

I've tried a few different yogurt places including Kiwi (didn't particularly like it).  This is the best frozen yogurt I've ever had.  Every time I go there I get the Salted carmel pretzel flavor... It's delicious!  I'm waiting for them to bring back the salted chocolate turtle flavor because that was even better.  They have every topping you could think of and the guy that is always there during the day is super friendly.
I have been coming to this place for years. I have moved up north, but every time I'm in the neighborhood I make it a point to grab my favorite sandwich.

Exactly what I was looking for tonight. After moving to Vegas 15 years ago from St. Pete, I wanted some fresh sea food and live 80's music. Jimmy's didn't disappoint. Great band playing my favorite 80's tunes and good seafood. I had the craw fish chowder, excellent! For my main course I had the seafood platter with grilled Grouper, Scallops and shrimp with a side lobster tail. Other than the Grouper being slightly over cooked, everything was very good. I have to remember this place for the next visit.

My go to spot when I want to go out and have some drinks but not go to a club or any place loud. Very nice ambience for drinks with friends or even a date night. Darker and candle lit at night. Pretty casual but more young professional crowd rather than college age. Bartenders are friendly and know what they are doing. More than just your basic bartenders that only know how to make typical shots or bar drinks. Here it is a craft and art and it shows. Drinks are always strong, beautiful, and tasty. Very simple, modern decor with a classy feel. Come around Christmas time for Miracle @ Mezzo and it's a completely different place with a different menu and the most lit Christmas party to be at for about two months.

This is a great place for lunch. Isn't too crowded and the food here is great. The drinks are pretty good as well. I ordered the Avocado toast with eggs and my husband ordered their steak and eggs, both orders were pretty good. We also ordered the Brussels sprouts, which is one of my favs!

I won't even say bad customer service, but lack of comprehension was performed today by Boss Lady Vicki herself!

The process was fine, she informed me of the issue with my nails turning yellow which occurred from my last encounter at Nifty because the technician missed applying gel on my nails and I didn't notice it until I was gone...but I didn't come back and cause rage but moving along.

Issue #1 - As Vicki is using the nail drill, she starts twisting my thumb. I was trying to correct my thumb but she wants to inform me that it has to be painful for her to get it done; so it doesn't get completed because it HURTS! She then goes forward with her defense that she is not saying anything to me when ALL I SAID WAS YOU ARE HURTING MY THUMB! Didn't know if that would involve words but...yea

Issue #2 - As Vicki is applying my polish she has to use a UV lamp which she is throwing it from side to side as she finishes each hand, which results in a messed up nail because if you can imagine a person throwing something it tilts on my nail. I have her to correct it and she smacks her lips. I then go on to ask if there is animosity from (Issue #1) have one of your peers to finish. Her response is...no one is available (as I am looking at several workers talking and sitting at their stations). So like most customers I reference the boss can sure help me if you're being rude and Vicki says the following, "Do you know who the boss is? I say no who is the boss and she says, "Me". I ask for her name and she then declines. So at this point I just stood up to ask for another worker, because I couldn't sit there and be taunted by The Boss herself any longer. So then she gets up and storms to the back of the building.
