Thank you to the technician that came in to complete my nails and advise me her name. Meanwhile as the tech is helping me she is talking to another customer about me. (Really professional) Repeating she didn't say anything to me. Vicki, you are absolutely right, however, there is this word called ACTIONS that you loudly expressed from hurting my thumb and throwing your UV lamp in frustration. She really wanted to express her innocent role with the African American bully today. Kudos.

We stayed here for 2 nights. It's your typical Courtyard. While the valet was friendly and upbeat when we pulled up, the woman at the front desk was anything but. She wasn't rude, but she certainly lacked emotion and enthusiasm. No hello, just stated at me when I walked up. Checked us in but never told us anything about the property or the area. Actually, the only thing she says was our room number. Not very welcoming. 

But security is the real problem. Next day my key demagnetized (presumably too close to my phone). I went to the desk, gave the woman my key and said "this stopped working. Can you reset it fir room XXX."  She took the key, never asked for my name or ID, never said a word, and handed it back to me reset for the room number I gave her. There are lots of problems with this, including the fact that any non-guest who can get a key card can simply walk to the desk and give the number of any occupied room and they're in. Couple this with no safes in the room and you have the potential for some real problems. 

Come on, Marriott. Train your desk staff to be more engaged and to do their jobs properly.

By far one of the friendliest and tastiest restaurants in Boise. Great atmosphere, authentic fresh food, and just a fun place to eat. Hope this place is open for decades! Best curry in town hands down.

Tasty, but over-priced.

I popped in for lunch and ordered a mango chicken salad.  After a pretty lengthy wait, the salad came was delivered.  I was a little disappointed to find that it contained very little chicken and mango.  I had to douse it in salsa from the bar to add substance.  The flavor was there, but the value wasn't.  I don't see this place lasting long.

I really like the food they have, the bar lounge is really nice. They have a really good wine selection
 The movie selection is amazing, I mean there's things that are still playing at the theaters and the location is really nice because you can walk to all the fun on Broadway Street and you can also call a shuttle and they will go pick you up wherever you are.

I decided to check this place out on a recommendation.    I'm so glad I did.  The food was so tasty. I went with two friends and sampled their food and yum. Not one single bad tasting food.  Safe to say you can order whatever and won't be disappointed 

We had the chips.  Ok we had two tasty bowls with medium salsa but it was a little spicy 

I had the seafood enchiladas for dinner. Perfect portion size 

It's a BYOT (tequila) so we did.  $12 pitcher of margaritas are available in different flavors.  We had strawberry and mango

Had the Churros and homemade ice cream for dessert. The ice cream was so creamy that you can tell it was made in house.   The churro was still warm.

Definitely make a reservation. The place is S.M.A.L.L.  And filled up quick on a Friday night.

Our waitress was awesome but a bit slow.  Luckily we didn't mind since it was moms night out.  

I'll post some pics to make you drool :)

After seeing a bubble in my tire and the wire coming out with no spare tire and knowing that they close in 30 minutes..Michelle and Alex were caring enough to take care of me and stay to do it. I was so amazed at the kindness shown. I was not over charged or scammed into more purchases.  I am definitely going to go back and put my trust in these girls. Thank you Alex and Michelle! You rock!!!!

Disappointed & based on other reviews we expected more. A tire on our vehicle had begun to lose air, we knew it was a long shot but stopped in the Les Schwab Tire Center, 1405 E Prater Way, Sparks, NV 89434 to see if they could accommodate us. 

They  assured me they could take care of us before they closed & took our information, we were told they would get to us. After waiting & waiting & hearing nothing from the staff (we never heard anything from them) we departed. 

We were able to inflate the tire at another location to get us passed the emergency & we will deal with the tire later but we won't be returning to Les Schwab.

I'm a big fan of brunch so I'm on a constant hunt for great brunch places in St. Louis. When my friend and I happened upon Pomme, I thought I'd have another restaurant to add to my short list of brunch places. 

Unfortunately, this would not be the case.

I got Pomme's version of my go-to brunch fare: eggs benedict. Never fails to disappoint but Pomme's version did disappoint... a lot. First of all, they trimmed the eggs to the max and left solely the poached yolk atop my "benedict." Second of all, the bacon, which is actual bacon and not the Canadian bacon (ham) that's most often served with in eggs benedict, didn't complement the dish very well. Its crunchy texture made it hard to eat with the English muffin and the eggs so I had to eat it on the side, which was not how I had intended to have my bacon. Apparently Pomme is not a place where I can have my bacon and eat it too. Third of all, the wait was inexplicably long for poached eggs and a salad. Granted the salad had hanger steak on it but with how empty the restaurant was about 5-10 minutes after we were seated, the long wait seemed bizarre.

I don't think I'll be returning here any time soon and will thus resume my hunt for a good brunch place in St. Louis.

Oh, New China ! I love New China and let me tell you why. I enjoy their open sushi bar buffet, they have tons of interesting lunch and dinner options, I really like their their seafood selection - mussels, fried octopus, crab salad with cheese, shrimp in butter sauce with zucchini and cauliflower, abalone, sauteed salmon. Noodles are awesome, chicken and beef are good, too. 
Love their "tiramisu" style coffee cake, which is heaven, and soft-serve ice-cream. New China IS the place to feed my whole hungry family and brighten up a hectic working day. Always crowded, very colorful and multiethnic. Attentive waitstaff, interesting decor, and a lovely big chandelier right above the front register desk.
I don't honestly know where all the negative reviews come from. Never had a problem .

Here is the deal- no its not in the easiest place to get in and out of, but good lord the food makes up for it. This is serious steak sandwiches we are talking about that melt in your mouth. The lemonades are just great also. Take a chance and try it out - you will not be dissapointed.

I love that we are having all sorts of new places opening in my hood! This is no different. Here are some pros and cons of the Parkmoor after two visits:

PROS
- Easy online ordering for curbside and quick delivery of meal
- Outdoor seating that is well spaced (not all gathered in a small area)
- Walk up window to order sno cones
- DELICIOUS sno cones, tons of flavors and sizes, and optional boozy sno
- Delicious fries
- Good portions
- Husband loved the burger

CONS
- Vegetarian options severely lacking. Would love a veggie burger, adult grilled cheese, or a more substantial salad
- Kids grilled cheese was not good (american on white bread)
- One of my big memories from the old Parkmoor was vanilla malts. No shakes/malts on the menu.

Will I be back? Yes for sno and fries, but would love to see those veg options for a full meal to appeal!

For our last night in NOLA, we wanted something classic, something fancy, something that oozes 'NEW ORLEANS' from it's very foundation. 

Commander's Palace fits that bill. 

We arrived early for our reservation, so we went to their small bar in the back (through the kitchen, escorted by an employee) and started the evening with cocktails. They were very insistent to take our time, our table would be ready when we were. I had The Adelaide Swizzle...it was one of the best mixed drinks I've ever had. I had a few more throughout the night, as well as the Crescent City Cooler which, despite the cheezy name, was ultimate refreshment in a glass. 

When we were ready, the bartender called the maitre'd and someone was sent back to collect us. Another short jaunt through the kitchen (which is always so educational!) and we were seated in the main dining room. 

The restaurant is beautiful; with fabric paneled walls, wooden chandeliers and beautiful wall paper. The tables are spaced apart just right; you overhear no one else's conversation. 

The menu is compact and complete; all the bases are covered with just enough originality to make it seem fresh, but not grandiose. 

The wine menu is overwhelming in it's choice and has many price points for all budgets. We went with a pinot noir that our waiter recommended, based on our tastes. We were both very pleased. 

I started with the turtle soup. Take me home and put me to bed; I still think about that turtle soup. Light and nearly citrusy but warm and earthy at the same time. Perfection. 

My main course was a fried soft-shell crab. Sadly, I didn't enjoy it that much. It was served with avacado and other cool vegetables and it just didn't seem to match the crab well. The flavors were off for me. My husbands infused pork was incredible. 

For desert, we went big and got the table-side prepared bananas foster *and* the bread pudding souffle. The table-side preparation was quite the show; fun to watch and even more fun to eat. It was extraordinary; perfectly caramelized, with just enough alcohol still left to give it depth. The souffle my husband wouldn't let me touch; he's a bread pudding fanatic and this was, apparently, the best he'd ever had.

I enjoyed my experience at the Commander's Palace from start to finish, soup to nuts. The service is perfect, the food was excellent, the drinks, both mixed and wine, were right on point. A very satisfying experience.

Tacodelphia is a conveniently located corner spot on Broad St. in South Philly. After seriously craving Mexican food to the point of hanger, we landed on Tacodelphia as it offered a quick place to grab a few tacos to avoid the rush of other popular Mexican spots before hitting the town for the night. Before I get into the food, be advised this place doesn't have a restroom! 

The people working were extremely nice, and really loaded up my chicken quesadilla, which tasted a lot better than it looked. It was served with a side of habanero salsa, which was very good and about a 6.5/10 on the spice scale. 

My boyfriend was absolutely devastated to hear that they had just run out of al pastor (good sign I guess) and had to settle for 2 barbacoa tacos and a carnitas taco. While they offered a ton of toppings you don't see at your every day fast-casual Mexican (including pickled onions), the meat and tortillas left a lot to be desired. The state of the tacos combined with a heavy hand on the salt for the tortilla chips was the reason behind my three stars.

Dr. Mayra Lopez es la mejor doctora de familia que he conocido. Súper atenta, se preocupa por el paciente y se toma su tiempo en conocerte. Ella está empezando su clínica nueva en Clearwater y cobra solamente $60 por visita a pacientes sin seguro, lo cual es grandioso. La recomiendo a cualquier persona. También acepta Medicare Libre y Florida Health Solution. Prontamente tendrá más seguros. Te atienden en español.

Dr. Mayra Lopez is the best family doctor I have met in my life. She truly cares about her patients and takes the necessary time to know you. She is starting her own clinic in Clearwater, and right now it is only $60 for patients without insurance. She currently accepts free selection Medicare and Florida Health solution as she is starting her own clinic, new providers will be available in the near future. Bilingual staff.
Absolutely love the vibe of this place. They have plenty of room to work and good prices on quality coffee.
Beautiful even in a drought. Great place for kids and fun photos. The turtles are an awesome contribution.

Pros: yummy food, great service, outdoor seating available, deeeelish hummus
Cons: None so far

I love the Canal Bistro.  I stopped in here last fall, not knowing it was Mediterranean.  The hummus and garlic fries are both very yummy.   I've tried the chicken shish platter each time I've been here because I think it's fantastic.  Juicy, flavorful and so fresh.  It's served with a pyramid (yes, a pyramid) of rice.  I like to put hummus, rice and chick on the pita and make a mini wrap.

The service is great!  Kara was my server last time, and my glass was never (even half) empty.  She was always checking on us making sure that we had everything we needed and were enjoying our food.  Kara was really a great waitress.

All in all, I love the food and the ambiance of Canal Bistro.  Sit outside if weather permits and enjoy people watching while eating some great Mediterranean grub.

The restaurant is overwhelmingly charming. It is decorated with lots of wood accents and family photos. You feel very much at home as soon as you sit down. The fountain drinks are from a local soda brand, and they have a wide variety of options for local alcoholic beverages as well. Their menu is creative and delicious. They have numerous options for meat lovers and vegetarians alike. Everything was seasoned to perfection and the portions were generous. Their sandwiches have a wide variety of meat options like bison and pork, and their duck wings were delicious. There were eight people in our party and the service was exceptional. Drinks were refilled seamlessly and recommendations were made as asked, all of which proved to be delicious. Even their version of a BLT (typically a pretty safe, but forgettable choice at restaurants) with added avocado and a special sauce had an amazing flavor with a slight kick. Prices were reasonable and the atmosphere was relaxing. I would highly recommend to anyone as a great way to experience local drinks and creative cuisine in a positive and memorable way.

Think the "Everyone knows your name" song when you bring your dog in for care at Velvet Bow. The owner,  Vikki, and her very great staff love and recall every dog that comes into their shop. They provide excellent grooming and stand by their professional service. My dogs love "going to see Vikki."

Gotten a bit pricey!  Enjoyable, not but was better before so commercialized.  They used to do great things fir schools & field trips.  This was when ownership changed / nothing to do with Covid.  $$$$$

I grew up going to the old Bodo location and it was always tasty and a treat for my family but this Cafe Ole is a far cry from that great restaurant of my youth. Now this, this is where it went downhill. I sat down with my daughter as my stomach yearned for beans. I ordered the enchilada ranchero with chicken and dug in. I went straight for those beans..those damn beans. My tastebuds? Unimpressed! Was this a joke? So many questions ran through my mind. They were flavorless. Lifeless. Bland. Were they spiced by Satan himself? No...even he would have more flavor! The rice was no better. Beans. The backbone of any Mexican restaurant. Get those wrong and you've gotten everything wrong. Service was good. But the food... it's unjustifiable. It's a lovely restaurant. What a shame.

Butter in a squeeze bottle! So convenient! This place is a delicious greasy spoon.  They have everything when it comes to sandwiches, burgers and breakfast. The bacon is perfection, I had to order another round because it made me sad when I finished them all. I was really tempted to order even more bacon after the second round because it was that good! Along with my pancakes, I also tried the chocolate banana milkshake which was phenomenal! It had chunks of real banana in it. It was so good my friend forced me to share it with her. No iced coffee except for hot coffee poured over ice. The spoon they gave me to mix milk in my to-go cup of coffee had some food crusty bits on it but thankfully I didn't really need to use it. You also walk up and pay in the back. Good food at an affordable price. The restaurant was busy on this Saturday morning but the two of us  did not have to wait and it wasn't overcrowded. Totally want to come back and try a burger late night.

If I could give no stars I would!  The most non professional people you'll ever come in contact with claiming to be a business. They are a huge joke and bigger liars!  If you rent from this place after this review.... You deserve to get scammed and lied to.  I am calling them out on their bull----!  We showed up on a morning we rented a 20 ' pontoon boat.  It was very foggy we drove an hour and 45 mins to get there.  They told us we couldn't go out yet, which we understood. However, our question to them was"why didn't you call us?  (It would had been nice to sleep an hour longer). They said we were waiting to see if you showed up.  We went for coffee came back and Austin said" oh, for your trouble we bumped you up to a larger boat at no cost" we said thank You and proceeded on with loading the boat.  Tim had about as much personality as a wall.  He spoke in a condescending tone as he made sure to ask each of us to wipe our feet on the wet dirty towel they threw done on the floor.  We rent at least 6-8 boats a year on the gulf since moving here.  My husband and I have been boat owners in the past, when we got together, we both had a boat and we took good care of our boats. You don't need to be a condescending messenger Tim. 
The boat was the worst boat we have ever rented, no speedometer, no gas gauge, no radio, no backs on the seats, no cup holders.  It was like renting a raft with cloth sides, no joke.
The positive for the day was the area, it was peaceful and tons of dolphins to watch.  Also the fishing was good. 
When we arrived back 30 mins. Early we unloaded the boat, used the restroom and went on our way(My husband finished dealing with Austin while I was in the restroom).  After being told they would drop the price from 250.00 down to 150.00 they charged us the entire 250.00 plus gas. If you want to go out in this area there are plenty other marinas to use.  Do not be scammed like we were take your business elsewhere.  Do yourself a huge favor.  Austin and Tim all I have to say to you is shut down your marina....you guys are a HUGE JOKE!  Quit calling yourselves a business.  I called our bank card last night they will be disputing the charge !

Needed to find a new nail salon cause my old one started raising their prices. As soon as I walked in I noticed how beauty he decor is. The staff is also super friendly. Absolutely in love with this place! Will definitely be coming back.

Literally the worst experience ever! We got in line at 9:30 it's currently 1:15 am and G-Eazy still
Hasn't performed idk who's bad it is but either him or the night club they are the worst this made me dislike him and my first time in Reno! Who makes there fans wait for over 3 hours and not to mention he's been on the stage for over 45 minutes drinking with whoever while the DJ plays music... DO NOT WASTE YOUR TIME OR MONEY! We have a baby we had to plan this overnight trip, what a waste. SO DISSAPPOINTED

Largest sporting goods store in the world, or so they claim. I've traveled quite extensively and I've never seen a larger one, if that means anything. This isn't really just a sporting goods store, though. Sure, they do have a large selection of both adult and children's sporting goods and hunting, fishing, and camping gear, but it also has a...

cafe offering Starbucks coffee, an impressive array of fudge, gelato, and lunch items

ferris wheel, $1 per person (must be 36" to ride) 

array of taxidermied animals to view

several statues of U.S. Presidents, each plays a recorded message as you walk by

tropical aquarium that you can walk underneath...you have to see it appreciate it

there are also home decorating goods, a shooting gallery, and a nascar simulator

I last made a purchase here on 7/29/2012 and I had excellent and friendly service in both the women's running shoe department, as well as the fudge counter. haha Yes, if you are gonna eat fudge it's a good idea to invest in properly fitted running shoes. 

Especially love their selection of Ugg shoes, boots, and handbags as well as Northface and Under Armour. I don't play volleyball, but their selection of ladies volleyball shorts was great. 

This is a good place to bring the whole family, as there seems to be something (actually a lot of things) for everyone.

No scuba or surfing gear, most likely because there is no ocean nearby, but they do have snorkeling gear and water skis.

Prices are comparable to REI, Any Mountain, Footlocker, Nordstrom, et al.
Run down salon stylists are always on their phones everyone looked frumpy and not put together. Def got the typical cheap cut mall vibe not a profresh SPASATION  experience.

My 19 year old daughter took a very well maintained Cadillac to this garage for a "once over".  The Cadillac was my late father's, was pampered, and kept in a garage for 99% of its life.  It had only 27,000 miles on it. The day after the car was tended to by this shop, the lower panel of the dashboard on the drivers side came off.  Upon investigating it, there was green glue that was holding it in place, and the glue appeared shiny and new.  When my DAUGHTER took this back to this FEMALE OWNED and OPERATED business, the owner denied that her mechanics did anything to this area of the car.  My daughter then took the car to our old mechanic in St. Petersburg who stated that the glue put there to hold the dash in place was most definitely new.  Very disappointed in this outfit.  I will not return to this shop and would not endorse anyone to give them business.  How shameful for this business to take advantage of a 19 year old girl, especially given the owner prides herself on being a female in a male dominated industry.

Expensive but amazing burgers 
The best burgers out there! 
The waffle fries are extra crispy and not overly salted.. 
He chili is a 10! 
Don't forget to get a malt afterwards!! 
A family fav.

I recently had a new procedure called Facetite, recommended and performed by Dr. Shienbaum. Due to recent squaring off of my jowls, rounding of my face and excess fat underneath my chin, I felt it was time to refresh my appearance. This procedure not only got rid of the excess fat and laxity of my jowls but tightened as well. It has given me a revived facial shape and slimming appearance.  Since having the noninvasive Facetite procedure with Dr. Shienbaum I have received many compliments and regained confidence in my facial appearance, I couldn't be happier.

I have been a client of Dr Strickland's since 2006. He has always helped me with all my aches and pains. Most recently I was in so much pain I could not sleep lying down and had to use crutches to walk. I am off my crutches and sleeping well at night. I would recommend them to anyone.

If you want a horrible experience, but good food, come here. I had a 7:30 reservation, and checked in. The host was clueless, and while I was still standing there in front of him, he thought I was a new customer, and asked for my reservation again. He then told us it would be a few minutes, so we went to the bar. After 30 minutes, I checked in with the host again, who looked like a deer in headlights, and told me he did not have us checked in. We were finally seated about 15 minutes after that (45 minutes after our reservation, and after checking in 3 times). After we were seated, it took another 15 minutes for a server to greet us, and another long wait before we ordered. Had to request bread, being that we were starving, and was not sure how long we would be waiting for food. I was in my 1st trimester of pregnancy, and feared I may not make it out in time to deliver the way things were looking so far. We ended up getting our entrees over 2 hrs after our reservation. I will say the food was very good, but would never go back based on this experience.

So I did the endless champagne. I can't remember the brand but it was a brut. Not my favorite but it was more than tolerable. I had a duck hash and eggs, and the duck and eggs was phenomenal. However, the hash was too mushy and clashed really badly with the texture of the duck confit and the sunny side up eggs. It was also paired with diced sweet potatoes that were decent. The best thing at my table was the soup of the day: a shrimp and mirliton bisque.... *chefs kiss. It had such a great complexity and the flavors blended so well. Amazing. We also had the crab cake crepe. It was an interesting flavor and the lump crab was really fresh but not my favorite.

Lots and lots of meatballs and side dishes are awesome  
Fried Chicken balls to beef or Vegan, little bit of everything.  Nice sauce selection.  Beer & Wine only

We were looking forward to a movie on a long weekend to Nashville area. We thought we would see Ant Man since it opened last weekend.  So we splurged for 3D at $16/ticket.  I was a little miffed upon using Fandango that I couldn't use a digital ticket and had to stand in line for my paper ticket.  I wouldn't have paid for the convenience fee if I still had to stand in line.

We were excited to see the size of the theater from the outside, expectant to have an awesome experience.  Well, we were greatly disappointed.  Any Man 3D was in some small "sub-theater" in the very back whereas the regular version was in the biggest theater in the complex!  I would not have paid this much for tickets for such a small theater.  Bad form, Carmike!

I made an order on the Online Pizza Portal on 7/12/19. It said pick up time was 9:10 p.m. I never did receive a push notification that my order was ready, so about 30 minutes later, I decide to go pick up my order. When I got to the store, there were quite a few people waiting. When I asked if my online order was ready, the young man told me, I don't know. When I asked what he meant by that, he then asked what I ordered. After telling him my order, he looked around in the hot and ready section, then he yelled to the back crew if my order was ready. I assume the back crew said no because he never did give me my pizza and proceeded to help other customers. Other customers in the store said they had been waiting for their order for more than 45 minutes. I observed the back counter with pizzas sitting there. After about 10 more minutes, the young man looked through the pizzas sitting on the back counter and asked me what I ordered and my name. He then gave me the pizzas. The whole time I was in the store and probably waiting at home, my pizzas were sitting on the back counter. How hard is it to place the pizzas in the Pizza Portal? This has already happened to me a few times, so I refuse to wait if I make an online order and I gave them sufficient time to make my order. They are always very disorganized here and don't have the pizzas ready. I have been waiting for the survey link to work to give my comments, but it doesn't work (LittleCaesarsListens.com). This location needs a tighter game plan since it is busy here. I will not come here unless changes are made. I do like the pizza so they get a star for that.

Great Mexican food! Delicious ceviche and tacos! And their horchata was perfect! Exactly what I was looking for! The people their were super hospitable and friendly and the service was great too! Will definitely be back!
Great place to go for a romantic dinner!  Beautiful view of downtown at night.  Be sure to make  reservations first as they can get very busy. Highly recommended!

Visited for the first time this evening for a Facebook event "meditation with chickens".  Got to hold and feed multiple fancy chickens! Very cool. Way cooler than goat yoga!  Enjoyed kombucha and iced happy tea. Will be back.

Lovely little breakfast spot & charming inside.  We had a street performer saxophonist the morning we were there which added to the charm.  Hubby & I shared the Cajun hash browns & an order of benigets.  Both were good- the benigets were more dense than other benigets but still tasty.

For $85 this was really a terrible experience. Out of the 4 dishes we ordered, 3 were wrong. And not just a little wrong, completely wrong. 

My mother in law is allergic to eggs. She ordered the burger and asked them to leave off the egg because she's extremely allergic. We said it 2x. Her burger came out with a fried egg on it. She said she wanted it well done, it was medium rare. 

I ordered the St. Bart's POACHED eggs. It came out with SCRAMBLED eggs on top. 

My daughter ordered the kids meal with pancakes and scrambled eggs. This meal came with a drink. She got French toast and NO egg. AND the server charged us an extra $3.50 for her orange juice!!!

That's just the issues with the ordering. There was no manager apology, and the waitress said she normally works the night shift which is why she got everything wrong. 

Ok so let's talk about the food. The poached egg was barely cooked- the yellow is supposed to be soft and runny, but the whites are supposed to be cooked. Instead I was eating a cold runny egg, and I could even send it back because my husband was already done eating since his order was the only one they did right. The croissant was soaked completely through so it was a mess. The hash browns were cold, so clearly they just used my original plate. My biscuit was heavy and floury. Yuck. 

My daughter said IHOPs pancakes tasted better. And I have to agree. These pancakes were not fluffy at all. They tasted like they were made with wheat flour. And the scrambled egg looked like it was made with powdered egg. 

The dad's steak special tasted good but it was a total rip off at $24. The steak portion was tiny. For that price, we would rather go to Ruth Chris and get a real steak. 

Overall, it was a very disappointing Father's Day brunch.

This company promises fast internet speeds. They do deliver most of the time but it's frustrating when they go out. Once in a while it's ok but when it became a regular occurrence out where we lived, it was time we switched. Their cable box and menu is so outdated too. Also when I moved into my new house that had Charter internet hook up already, their tech said he didn't know how to set up the network and that I would have to contact another installer... Really? The equipment is from your company... and you basically set up on the same lines...

I love Seoul Fresh and have only come to the mall to eat here!! I have tried all the items on the menu and they are all delicious! Fresh food, large portions, excellent customer service, and great quality!  I am Korean so I know good Korean food! I am also amazed at house clean their work area is. Try some of the fun drinks they have out. I recently tried the Rose Lemonade and the Cherry Cola and both are very good! If you have not been, then you must go!! Best food court restaurant by far!!

We found lice and this being the second time around, with the resistance lice, we needed some help. We quickly got an appointment for the same day. The process was explained very thoroughly. 

We had a great experience, much quicker than doing it ourselves! It isn't a quick fix but it is not toxic and gets the very worst of the symptoms straight away. The treatment plan is much simpler as well. Thank you!

So, after living in Fox Chase forever, I finally bit the bullet & ventured into this "Haus". The decor is definitely authentic/old. We were seated upstairs, which is very "Flowers in the Attic". Complete with old dusty wood scent. We changed tables twice bc they were ridiculously wobbly. The upholstery is gnarly & just plain old dirty. The server was in an anxious rush..made us feel uncomfortable @ times. From the overpriced menu, we ordered a couple of "authentic"  dishes..overall the food arrived hot & well seasoned. Just nothing I would absolutely "have to have" again. The best part was their beer list. The dessert choices were literally store bought American cakes & pies. We hoped to enjoy a genuine Austrian Danish or strudel. Needless to say we will not be returning.

Great food and great place, the food was delicious. I had the fried chicken and green beans and mac n cheese. All were delicious. Everything stayed hot in my 15 min commute back to my house too, which is very impressive.
The owners were super kind and excited to have us in, they were super conversational and wanted to tell us all about their food, I loved that they took so much pride in their restaurant, the food was definitely made with love!

This is a pricey breakfast brunch place with pretty long lines after 930. It is probably worth a visit if you have never been there but I would not really go out of my way for it because the crowds get overwhelming. The food is reasonably good however it can get very pricey quickly if you order any extras subs as coffee, orange juice , whipped cream, syrup etc and it is easily over 50$ for the people. The location is also not the best as it's in the bottom of a non descript grey building with minimal street parking as well as sketchy people walking around.

This is a new favorite of ours! We live on the far east side, and we're happy to drive to SoBro to enjoy this place. I was hoping they take reservations, but it didn't appear that they do. We went on a Saturday evening, and it was really busy! We got seated at the large table on the bar side. It's a popular spot since it's family friendly. Even though it was busy, we were promptly greeted and ordered our drinks and an appetizer. 

I love their Peach Bourbon cocktail SO MUCH. I love bourbon, and the peach just gives it a spring/summer vibe, perfect for sipping on a patio here or elsewhere, to be honest. 

The bacon chorizo dates with red pepper sauce is one of the best appetizers I've had! You get 3 of them so it's a nice start to your meal without it filling you up before your entree arrives. 

I got the Honey Sriracha Crispy Gulf Shrimp bowl. The shrimp was perfectly done and just had the right amount of heat from the sriracha. The veggies were tender crisp so there were good textures throughout. My husband got the Cuban sandwich, and he liked it a lot, but he found it a bit dry. The housemade pickles were a highlight for him though. He said the sandwich could have used a bit more sauce (I'm not sure what sauce he's referring to though.) 

I haven't had the daily specials yet, but I am sure I'll come back and try those. Saturday it was the Cowboy burger. It's a nice change that their sandwiches come with simple salads instead of fries. One thing I wish is that they had a dessert menu. I have a big sweet tooth so I miss that, but I'm happy to substitute a peach bourbon for that. 

I like that they have parking next to the building and across the street. You can order to go, and there are 2 parking spots reserved for pick up orders. I'm so excited to see more places in this neighborhood away from the craziness of Broad Ripple Ave. Can't wait to come back!

The home of Indianapolis Indians became ground zero for my first baseball game experience. I don't understand the game very much but after being at the Victory Field, I'm gearing up for more of such experience including more lessons about the game. We were there for almost the entire game and then enjoyed some fireworks. Parking was easy and right across the street. The awesome weather, chilled shandy and chips and dips made it a fun Friday night at the stadium. Perfect start to my 2018 summer. Yay!

Y'all!!!! 
This food was sooooooooooo doggone on good.... I had to type DOGGONE!  
Y'all. Y'all. Y'all. They are wrong for this.  
I ordered the butter beans with fried chicken ($3 up charge) and my hubby ordered a fish plate, mac&cheese, with a bell pepper.  
I can't lie his bell pepper was a little to hard for our liking (because we eat the actual bell pepper, not just the stuffing).  Even with that, the food was extremely delicious and we were looking for the bed and it was lunch time. 
We ordered online with easy contactless, curbside, pickup.  

We'll be back and thanks for an amazing lunch that will carry over to dinner.

I have been to the local a few times and have always enjoyed it.  Last visit I noted they have changed a few of the menu items.  I tried the new toast appetizer with feta and avocado.  Loved it.  I also had the tuna club and it was different from last time.  Less bread and more mayo and bacon.... what's not to love about that change.  So when I need a burger and to watch some sports, this will still be one of my go to places.

This is our new favorite place for Mexican food. Bucks county has been lacking a place like this. We expanded our search a tad further out and found la Choza. Excellent variety on the menu (though - to be honest - I think they could cut a few things as I'm not sure they need to include pasta, lol. ). The chicken mole was to die for. We will definitely be back.

Dryer broke so to the laundromat we went. Washers, dryers and facility were clean. It was a little crowded on a Sunday afternoon I wasn't surprised though. The only reason I gave it 4 stars because it was hot in there like break a sweat while folding hot. Other than that great. The staff was friendly. The stay open until midnight. I'll use them for future heavy soiled or bulky king size washes. To save on time.

So good!  After eating a ton of Chinese I usually feel so gross but this place was amazing.  My sister and I ordered the string beans, dan dan noodles (8), and cumin chicken (6).  I think the numbered menu is very accurate describing HOW spicy dishes are.  I really wanted the spicy hot pot (10) but my sister wasn't feeling it.  Anyway, I totally agree that the spicy level isn't so intense that it overpowers all other flavors.  It's basically a party in your mouth.  DEFINITELY get the Dan Dan and string beans (ground pork comes on both).  If you like cumin, the chicken is also good.  Not too spicy at all.  Also, our service wasn't bad at all.  The water glasses were constantly full.  I personally hate when servers are all up in your business the whole time you are eating.  It took a little while to get seated but we went without reservations and it was pretty bumpin.  Can't wait to come back.

This place reminds me of Portland/Seattle. I only had one (gigantic) doughnut, the lemon icebox, it was a bit too sweet. Being a doughnut place I expected it to be on point. I recommend getting multiple chicken sliders because they are delicious. The bread is nice and the chicken is cooked perfectly! This place is busy, so I'd go before or after lunch time. You order at the counter and wait for your name to be called when your order is ready. There is free water available at the bar.
its your typical whole foods. i mean jesus. 3 star just because its your typical whole foods. what do you expect? flying monkeys?

Dr. Eyrich not only cares about getting results, he cares about people. He is a rare find for the Midwest with his blend of talents, gifts, and what he can offer you. If you are ready to get to the core of your health issues, have access to a brilliant healer and clean, natural supplements, this is your place. I went there for a hiatal hernia and digestive work and he has made a huge difference in the quality of my life!

Two stars because of the food/service connection. I ordered breakfast hash and inquired about the spiciness of the food specifically cayenne pepper. I was told they could leave the spice off. I felt shut down when I tried asking if it would still taste good. If a diner asks questions about the food it means they need help navigating the choices. 

The food arrived totally devoid of flavor. Not even salt and pepper. The server offered to take it back but that's a bit too late when you are trying to keep pace with your dining companion. And it's exactly the problem I tried to avoid by asking if it would still have flavor. 

There was exactly nothing to recommend about the meal for me. I hope this critique of service and food preparation illustrates that communication is important. Actually listen to what the concerns are when questions are asked instead of giving flippant answers without thinking. I'll come back but will try to sit at another server's station. 

This would be one star if I wasn't planning to try it again. It's a pleasant place to eat. Maybe I'll try the pancakes? Those looked pretty good.
My first experience in Bella Coast is the atmosphere is great  and the place is cute & clean place. I was sort of disappointed by the quality of the food. It could have been better.

Not impressed.  More like fast good quality really. Everything fried, and over-fried at that. Lots of grease. Even in the soup. It was like canned soup that was doctored up a little bit. It was gross. I wont be returning.

This place was given so many praises, that we figured it had to be the perfect place for a birthday dinner.  The Chef was touted so highly by those in the hotel that we figured it was worth a try.

Well we were wrong, and very sadly mistaken, as this turned out to be a less than celebratory place to have a Birthday dinner.

We ordered a lamb entrée and a salmon entrée.  The salmon was dry, and the lamb was OK, but the sauce was so greasy and salty that it was a shame to waste good lamb.  The potatoes were limp and tasteless, I felt they had been left over from the breakfast service.

We ordered a white wine, which was way overpriced, but hey this is a big hotel, and the money is always made on the wine and spirits, but 50 bucks for a bottle of New Zealand white wine, was very much on the pricey side.  Plus it was not served in a cooler, and this wine needed to be served ice cold for it to be good.

When we complained about our meal, they were very nice, they did take the cost of the lamb off the bill, but they also wanted us out of there so quickly they almost brought us the bill before we had telling them about our meal.  On top of that, since we were two males, they asked if we wanted separate checks.  When we said we wanted coffee, they brought us coffee (which was not so great either, but that may have been my taste buds from the greasy meal, and then we waited and waited for them to bring our check.

We did go in the next morning for the breakfast service, which was very nice, but nothing remarkable.  It was a big hotel breakfast buffet.

This place is not on our return visit list when we go back to Indy!

I purchased tires a year and 1/2 ago that where guaranteed for 50k Miles. Unfortunately they where bald after 25k Miles. I asked to speak to Todd Miriam the Mgr. I  explained the situation. Todd did his research and we both came to an agreeable solution. 
I have been going to Bob Lee's for Tires, Brakes, Oil changes and most of my automotive needs since the late 80's. 
They never disappoint.
Wonderful food and service. And amazing slider burger with the topping of egg and duck bacon.

THESE ARE SERIOUSLY THE BEST TACOS IVE EVER HAD AND IM NOT EXAGGERATING. I always order like 6-10 tacos just for myself cause they're that good. They're only there every Friday and Saturday and start around 7. There are so many cars there waiting for them because they're that good. I truly recommend this place because first of all it's local but their tacos are so good that it's unbelievable why you're not in heaven. The first bite I got into them buche tacos made me cry. I'm not exaggerating. I don't know what they put in their meat but it was just so delicious. These are the most legit tacos I've had and I've been to a lot of taco trucks cause I go taco truck hunting with my boyfriend. I'm glad to share this with everyone cause they deserve the credit. I truly and truly recommend buche tacos which are pork belly and the cabeza too. Just be open minded and don't just order the asada (which is also really good). Also they only accept cash but bring like $20 worth cause you're going to end up ordering a lot. GO GO try this place please! It's so good!
Loved this place. We went impromptu for a late, late lunch and had a great time. Come after 2:30 for a solid happy hour list and they were kid friendly. Excellent service and food was great.

I was getting ready to gear up for a big day of tireless apartment hunting on Wednesday and was trying to think of the best way to jump start my day, either going to my favorite coffee shop (where I used to work! Thank You!), or go treat myself to a belly full of a hot breakfast. Well I must admit that my stomach whining protestingly at just coffee I decided there was no better place to go than Sabrina's.

I have been there before on the weekend, so I know the wait can seem grueling. Knowing that it is such a popular place though I always find that calling before I leave the house to get on the waiting list really helps.

However this day was a weekday so I took my chances at not calling. I arrived at 9:30am and walked in to a mostly empty setting. Now since anytime I have gone before I've sat outside this was the first time I pierced the inner sanctum. It is actually quite large inside as the separation of dining areas makes for a deceiving outer appearance. When one of the servers saw us modestly peeking around a corner she happily ushered us into the hustle and bustle of the main (that day) breakfast nook. We sat down at one of the tables for two. And I have to say this was the only time I felt a little nervous. You see I am a bit clumsy ( okay a lot) and the confines of the claustrophobic table set me a little unease. The table had a bowl for creamers, a bowl for butter, sugar dish, ketchup, hot sauce, salt, and pepper. I understood the necessity so anytime my dining partner wasn't looking I just slowly pushed it closer to their side of the table.

Our waitress was prompt and bubbly just like a freshly squeezed orange juice and a fresh pot of coffee. I felt that this was the way that all of us should feel that early in the morning. Her service throughout our meal was impeccable and we left an extra big tip! 

Walking in I all ready knew what was to be ordered. I had coffee, Blue Cheese Frittata, Stuffed Caramelized Challah French Toast, and a side of scrapple (we decided to just split  things). The waitress brought out our delicious smelling meal and I was eager to devour as much as I could. They went so far as to even split the dishes in half for us! That was terribly convenient! This way there was no envious grumbling as one of us scarfed down one plate while the other looked on menacingly. The frittata was a giant fluffy slice of goodness. It has spinach, mushrooms, and bacon in it, along with blue cheese. Every bite was scrumptious and delicious. It was not dry (which I hate). The french toast is stuffed with banana and a farmer's cheese (which I find similar to a danish filling but, way better). The vanilla maple syrup is poured on at the perfect amount, not to little but, not drowning the entire dish either. The bread used is the largest I have come across, and I have seen giant Texas french toast in my day! It is a sweet taste for the breakfast enthusiast. I savor every crumb!

Even with two voraciously hungry people chipping away at the tasty delights, there was no way either of us could finish. The waitress gladly wrapped the rest of it up for us. Our bill was under $25 which for the portions and unrivaled taste I am more than accepting to pay. I really think that is a great bargain for great food, great service, and a great atmosphere!
Best dinner we have had  in Smyrna.  True Italian Cuisine . Can't wait to go back and try some more Specials. Service was excellent. This Gem is just what Smyrna needs .

This place was delicious! We went on a nite-out-staycation on a Friday night. A little spendy, but great quality for the price! My wife had the beef and I had the pork shoulder; we had draft beers and wine=all good! Definitely worth a visit! Place could use a little more heat, but it was a cold Reno night!

I can't believe this is the first time I have been here. Fantastic food. Great drink selection. Great service. And the Fried Homemade Oreo dessert is amazing. Potato skins like I have never had before and now I don't know if I can't eat other ones anymore. Great selection of reasonably priced scotch and whisky. The NY strip was cooked perfect as was the cod. Even the sides and sauces had a homemade flavor and style that was perfect with each dish. My wife and I eat out often and are very critical of food and service. This place is an absolute must try. You will love it.

I went to Lulu Chinese Express with friends a couple of days ago. One of my friends ordered a bowl with one entree and was given the wrong one, place was not busy so no excuse. I got orange chicken which was kind of blah and sesame beef which was premium and $1 more while still being totally pink in the middle. Such thin strips of meat should not be pink if they were properly stir fried. I do not eat pink meat. Dierbergs Lulu had never disappointed but this one did right away .

The food is very good. Service is another story. Very hit or miss. Today  after eight minutes of being at the table, that's according to the clock in the kitchen, I had to go find my server to place my order. Finished my water,three people walk by with a pitcher even refilled glasses at the table next to me,so as i was getting up to go to the bar to get a refill, server finally came to my table.  Everyone has days but this was not my first experience with sketchy service or what not and put it in a review. The Mr. croissant is wonderful. Love the smoked tomato

BEST BURGERR I'VE HAD IN DECADES!!! And the greens that we're put on the burgers were DA BOMB!!! The brioche bun was delicious!!! Only one problem...i live too far away to stop by as often as if like. I live near LAX Airport. But when I'm in the area...YOU KNOW!!!

The best way to describe the Sustainable Vines Wine Tour is with one word: Wow!!! We have been on quite a few wine tours, including wine tours in France, and this was easily the best wine experience we've had by far. I wish we can rate this higher than a five!

If you haven't been to the Santa Barbara area to do wine tasting, go now! Also, if you are thinking of heading out to the wineries on your own, you will be missing out on so much by not going on a guided tour. The Sustainable Vines Wine Tour will guide you through the Santa Ynez Valley in a way that is literally impossible to do outside of a tour. Scott, our tour guide and certified sommelier, has a vast knowledge of the local wine and his connections with area wine makers and vineyard owners make for a truly unique experience.

Here was our day's itinerary: 

Pick up in a super classy Mercedes touring van at 10:00am in downtown Santa Barbara. Sustainable Vines will pick you up from a variety of areas in the Santa Barbara region. The van proceeded to pick up seven other tour group members, for a total of nine in the group. Your lunch choices of sandwiches or salads from a local Santa Barbara eatery will be in stow.

Our first stop was a small private winemaker near  Buellton. This is not a winery stop that you would be able to make on your own. Scott has connections with the proprietor and wine maker. We tried about six or seven of their  wines -- all were superb. We preferred the Chardonnay and Cabernet Franc. 

The next stop was another private Vineyard. The Petite Sirah, in particular, was exquisite. We also dined on our lunch at an idyllic setting on top of a hill overlooking the vineyards. Truly perfect!

On our way to our third and last stop we took a detour and stopped at a local lavender farm. Again, amazing!

The last stop was Demetria Estate. Incredible views and fantastic wine. Scott also knows the vineyard owners and we were able to chat about the wines and have a tasting experience not available to others stopping by the vineyard. 

On our way back to Santa Barbara, Scott played the movie "Somm", which is a documentary about the sommelier business. It was a great way to pass the time on the ride back to the hotel. 

In sum, you will have a few options to choose from for wine tours in the Santa Barbara area. Honestly, this should be your first, second, and only choice. With Scott's knowledge combined with the unique experiences, you will have a fantastic story to tell and memories for a lifetime. 

Enjoy the Santa Barbara wine!!!

I bought them a sofa and after 3 months the fabric was cut and the wood broke and when I went to them they said that I need to send an email and actually sent an email with the pictures but did not care or respond to one and I contacted and sent several times but they do not repent. I advise you not to deal with them about a very bad experience with this place.
Very good Mediterranean food! I ordered takeout. It was ready in less time than predicted. Fresh and yummy!

Yay!!!! Cutest tiki bar ever!!! Super super cute. I ordered the Oxy-Colada and my boyfriend got the Pearl Diver. Both drinks were delicious but mine was better! Love the vibe here. Our bartender with the long hair was super friendly and chill. This bar is located on the 2nd flood of the Franklin Bar. Easy to find and the bouncer at the door was nice as well. Can't wait to go back again!

I like coming to this location. I usually order on the app and then go inside to pick it up. It's always ready by the time I get there, unless they are busy which is understandable. The drive-thru takes a very long time so if you don't like being in line for a whole, I would order ahead or go inside. One thing I have noticed lately is that when I order hot drinks, they aren't filled up all the way. With how pricey it can get at Starbucks, I wish they would fill the cups all the way. The tables are never clean either from what I've noticed, but I never dine in. Just a heads up for other people. Other than that, I've had pretty good experiences.
I give the rehab center one star.  If I could I would give this center a 0.  If you love your dog don't take him here.  If you doubt me, take him there and you will appreciate why I say this.

Saji is amazing. She is so sweet and professional. My wedding dress had several layers and she was able to alter them all to a perfect fit for my shorter frame. She also added a subtle bustle that was easy to work with and very practical. I would highly recommend her for all of your wedding dress needs.

I try to support local business but once again in regret. Every time I go in here, which is seldom, the prices and quantity is insane. The tab is of Applebees or T.G.I. Friday's. 3 pierogis with no sauce= $6, small side order of fries with cheddar cheese=$5, 4 mozzarella sticks=$7....Just examples of the prices. Why go to an expensive/local Joe Schmo diner when you can have a a level up dinner date somewhere else with your wallet..

Came here on a Sunday 8/9 as soon as they opened at 11:30 am. Perhaps thats not a good time to come in because they served us food that was likely made last night. 

We ordered beef scallion pancakes and the meat inside was fully cooked but completely cold. The outer layer was hot though. That tells me that they cooked it last night, put it in the refrigerator, and heated it up in the morning, which is gross. We told the waitress about it, and she brought it back microwaved because the meat inside then was warm but then the outer layer became soggy and no longer crunchy. 

The hot and sour soup was also cold. We again let the waiter know and they again put it in the microwave where certain parts of the soup became hot but it had cold spots within it. 

This is not the quality that Jane G used to have. I wonder if they changed ownership during the shutdown. I wont be coming back.
Updated: I increased to 4 stars. Now they are usually open in the morning (hope punctuality lasts through the winter) and not out of stuff. Plus still the most delicious and fairly fast.

I'm not a coffee drinker but loved watching them make it. Such an intricate process. I did get their chai tea latte and it was on point! Also the tomatoe and cheese pastry was different and very good!

Best people anywhere.   I have gone there twice.  From the moment you walk in and Sandra greets you with a smile and knows you by name until the time you drag your self out from exhaustion,  the positive atmosphere is beyond explanation.   I forget I'm in pain and need to get better.   I feel like I am at the gym working out with friends.   I am also being educated on why my injury is affecting me the way it is and how to get better.   The took me from a wheel chair to being able to run.   The people the are God sent.

This pertains to the Cherry Hill, NJ location. I LOVE Road Runner Sports. Each time I go there, I"m nearly immediately helped by friendly, knowledgeable employees. I'm an avid runner (45-50 miles a week), so I got fitted/assessed at this location for shoes. Since then, I have been going back for new pairs. Today Kristi helped me find a new pair of Brooks. She seamlessly took care of me and multiple other people; we all barely had to wait! Each time she was clear that she needed to run off to help someone else, but would be back very shortly. Super pleased.

Just returned from another visit.  Even though they were seriously short staffed, the people working were friendly and helpful.  The food was as good as it always is.  I know the pandemic has made things difficult for many businesses but Brew Brothers is still doing a great job in the face of adversity,

Was in town Friday night for a family girls weekend & Ike & Jonsey's rocked.  There was a Colts game going on so was pretty packed.  They played AWESOME music.  The place is a bar/restaurant with a smaller dance floor.  The crowd was a great mix, but mostly older 20's, mid 30's and even up to 60's.  Everyone got along great and when the dance music started going the dance floor got filled and was a blast.  The waitress we had was a tad on the rude side and when we asked to split the bill we got a big "SIGH".  Didn't eat here so can't comment on the food.  If you want a place with good cold beer & drinks and awesome 80's, 90's music where you can dance, this is your place.  I'd definitely come back here.  The one thing I did not like is that you can smoke in the bar.  Being from Ohio this is not an issue so for us non-smokers this may be a turn off.  There weren't a ton of people smoking, but there were some.  Overall a great time was had by all.

Not a bad family breakfast/lunch restaurant. Fair breakfast selection. Prices are a bit high for what you get. The service is fast and efficient with prompt refills on coffee and tea. I tried the Sonoran Benedict and the wife had the Sonoran skillet. My eggs were cooked well but the chorizo had a different taste. The topping was not as described on the menu in my opinion. Wife like hers and also agreed on the taste of the chorizo. In and out for $30.00 for a simple breakfast. Will go back sometime just not sure when.
Great place to take the kids. They have toddler time on Sunday mornings 9:30am-11am. Fun for all

Don't go here! It's dirty and always overcrowded. The classes are packed and the staff is rude. Also, cancelling your membership is a nightmare. I followed all the steps on the website and they still wouldn't cancel it and charged me for an extra two months. I had friends warn me but I went because it is the closest gym. Learn from me and DON'T DO IT!

Highly, HIGHLY recommend this place. One of the best Indian restaurants in Philly. They have a varied menu that includes a Vegetarian, South India, & an Indo-Chinese selection. The chaat menu, specifically the Bhel puri, is to die for! Definitely looking forward to the next visit. You won't regret giving the biryani menu a try either: The goat biryani made me miss home

Honestly everything here is AWESOME LOL. EVERYTHING soup, pot, fatty beef pot, quality of beef, sauce, utensils, bowls, anything you ever order. 

Some people complain about service, but I've never had a bad experience, its a Chinese restaurant I'd say its on the side of good service for a Chinese/ hotpot place.

Downside, expensive AF. This place isn't at all worth it if you aren't a hotpot obsessed person. 2 people here has always been over $100 (not counting wagyu  ect)

Every time I get the bill I laugh like HAHA WTF there must be a mistake, wait no.. im at about hotpot. I honestly complain but then... I keep coming back because it is the best hotpot in philly for sure no competition IF you dis regard price...

This is hands down one of my favorite restaurants in Reno. This quaint little eatery has always warmed my heart--and my stomach. The tomato bisque is probably the most popular & for good reason. I love to get it in a bread bowl or with a sandwich on the side, or if I'm really hungry, both! I've tried many different soups & sandwiches here & I have never once been disappointed. Tomato bisque & the BBQ chicken sammy are usually my go-to's. That, or the grilled cheese with all of the extras added. With the sandwiches come salad that is TO DIE FOR. The dressing is so delicious & will most likely win anyone over who isn't usually excited about greens. Not to mention the dried cranberries--yum! Last, but not least, the cute little house-made cookie that comes with each plate is the perfect ending to a delicious meal. I love that you can sit inside to enjoy the artwork & great music, or you can sit outside to enjoy the Reno Midtown atmosphere & sunshine. On top of everything, the staff is incredible, the table holders that have street names are adorable, & I have never encountered anything less than an immaculately clean environment. It's the perfect place for lunch with mom or some friends, a date, or even solo dining--I've done them all! I would & do recommend this to anyone looking for a Reno treasure. Thanks, Süp!

We stopped in yesterday to enjoy some wonderful Polish food and were not disappointed. 
We started out with the Pickle Soup, which was hot and delicious. Don't knock it until you have tried it...it is so flavorful.
This was served wiith warm bread.
For our entree, we aplit the Polish Combo plate for one (it is enough). We had a Golobki (cabbage roll), a polish smoked sausage, a small bowl of hunter's stew and 4 pierogis (of your choice). We opted for the potato and cheese pierogis topped with carmelized onions and bacon. We also added a side of sauerkraut. What a delicious meal. The service was also great....evdn though there was one woman manning the entire room, she was attentive and friendly. 
Growing up in a Polish household, this was a real treat. We will be back!

Stop all of your bitching folks. When you book a room for $34 dollars a night, do you expect the Ritz Carlton? Yes, the casino is "smoky", but so are most casinos. Besides, I came out $180 ahead on video poker. The rooms are huge and some have floor to ceiling windows and are generally very clean. The food is quite good, but if it doesn't suit you, you can walk to a local steakhouse and drop $150 for two people. Finally, if you book through Groupon, you get five free drinks and for those complaining about a resort fee of 12.99 a night.....you've never been to the Nugget, GSR, or most any other place in Reno or Vegas where it's close to $30 a night! And no, I don't work at the Sands or any of their other properties! Just sayin'!

I called Bob with a high level question about my spa controller board and he knew all the details.  He pointed me in the right direction for a fix even though that meant he wouldn't have to come out and wouldn't make any money.  His information was dead on and very useful.  I HIGHLY recommend his services.

This place is awesome and bound to become one of SB's best lunch spots. With both vegetarian and meat options, I can eat there with all of my friends. The food is so unique and tasty - it's really nice to have a place that doesn't just serve the same old sandwiches and salads. Plus, the spot on the roof of Antioch is a lovely, informal place to dine alone or with friends. Oh, and don't even get me started about the specialty cheesecakes and desserts. They are so tasty and decadent, you would NEVER KNOW they are vegan!

I flew in from Park City Friday for the long Memorial day weekend to be with my family.  I was feeling so unlike the "California Girl" I have been for my whole life.  My sister looked like she had been "kissed by the sun".  I just had to find out where she had been.  I on the other hand, looked like Snow White.

You MUST visit Lisa's European Sun in Goleta!!  It is AMAZING.  Lisa, (the owner) made me feel so very special.  I did  a "cocktail" in the stand up (great bulbs) and then the Mystic Spray Tan.  She gave me a band for my pony tail and extra nets as I wanted to protect my fair hair.  She could not have done anything more to make me feel more pampered.  I also had extra towels for the Mystic  so the bottom of my feet would not stain  The cleanliness, quality of service, products and ambience made me feel like a million bucks.  Thank you Euro Tan.  I will be back.  I highly recommend your business to anyone who wants a pleasant and joyful experience. Plus, I made a new friend!
Patricia Andrews,
Park City, Utah
What an amazing place!!! The food and the service was great.  Can't wait to go back. To get the red snapper!!!

We were here for birthday brunch and Nolan our server hit all the right notes. The food was excellent and our special request to turn fish&chips into fish tacos was executed perfectly. Our birthday girl was very happy and our puch happy to celebrate with us too. Birthday beignies were delicious and hot. Prices were very reasonable, we will be back!

This gym is great and has flexible membership options.  There is always equipment available, no waiting for a machine, no time limits.  Everything is clean and in good condition.  Staff is super friendly and helpful.  Best gym I've been to in a long time.  Thank god I don't have to go to the UCSB rec cen anymore!

Always friendly. Always clean. Always delicious. Always wearing masks. I drive across town to go to the one on Dorsett rather than the one closer to me because of the reasons I just mentioned. Consistent always!

I don't Yelp often but this visit deserves a review! The #1 priority when I knew I was coming to Nashville was to get my mouth on some Nashville Hot Chicken and boy! Milk & Honey's Hot Chicken & Waffles did not disappoint! Please visit this spot if you're in town-you won't be disappointed. The atmosphere, the service, the beverages, and the food - amazing across the board!

This gorgeous new brewery welcomed guests with some lovely new beers, a tasty restaurant with a huge menu and an upstairs beer museum. Perfect trifecta!! We went on a rainy day and sampled some of the beers but will be back on a sunnier day to sit outside and sip some beers and schedule a beer museum tour. Fun place!

I've lived in Santa Barbara for over 10 years and only just now found this place!  The service was great and the selection was great.  They helped me put together the costume I was looking for down to the last detail - a cane!  I can't recommend this place enough.  I have a storage unit full of old costumes that I bought over the years - it's nice to have the option to rent now.

We absolutely LOVE the rings we have from Diamonds Direct. They are stunning, beautiful and seem fair priced. After visiting pretty much every store in the area, we settled here. Our experience with customer service/purchasing has unfortunately not been as great or if for sure give 5 stars. My fiancée/husband has never received any outreach or follow up (and we actually wanted it!) and even after inquiring in person in the store, we still didn't receive a phone call like we were told we would. Hoping this improves with the sale of the company from Distinctive Diamonds to Diamonds Direct and we can continue shopping here for future jewelry because their selection is very nice!

Best sausage egg and biscuits in town!!
The make the best home made biscuits yet! Got two this morning about 330am on my way to work! 
Good friendly people, even that early in the morning :-)

We tried Season's Pizza for lunch.  The interior cries for updating.  There was some work put in to the mural on the back wall, but overall, the decor was dated, including peeling wallpaper.  

We had thought we made a mistake, but decided to order nonetheless.  The Mediterranean Panini was really good, lots of flavor and one of the better paninis that we found in the places along the Concord Pike.  

Our waitress was nearby to keep our water glasses filled and the tasty Parmesan-dusted rolls were an unexpected treat.  

The three of us were able to get lunch for under $20.  A superb value along a restaurant crowded row.
Local, local, local. Food was good, service was beyond stellar, and the local brews were GREAT. Thank you to the staff that was working when we showed up. Will be back.
Our favorite swedesboro quick eats place. Love the buck a shuck oysters on Wednesdays. Crab fries are delicious and so are their flatbreads. Love that they have gluten free options, too.

Indy tire is great! I told them my tire was losing air and they took it into the bay to see what the issue was. A nail. The nail was in a part of the tire that couldn't be fixed with a patch. So they had to replace the tire.. which was fine because I had the road hazard warranty on my tires! (Everyone should have this warranty on their tires). With today being a day before a holiday, they were pretty busy. I had asked what a certain machine did for tires. The manager took me back to show me what the mechanic was doing and what the machine did (it was balancing tires). So I walked out with a new tire and new knowledge on tires! I highly reccomend!! Everything went smooth from scheduling the appointment to getting the new tire. I won't go to anyone else.

Houlihans is a good place to have lunch and I mean lunch by lunch items.  You know, the stuff no one can really cook badly (buffalo wings, burgers, fries, etc).

I went there for dinner recently and it was just a bad experience.  There was a small wait (small compared to TGIFriday's where I just should have waited).  When we finally got out table, it was not clean.  It took our waitress a good 10 minutes to clean the table.  Too bad I don't remember her name... but anyways... She did bring the menus after cleaning the table so that was good.  She took our orders, and brought our drinks and food.  That's when we noticed we had no silverware.  We told her this and it took forever for her to bring that out.

Finally our food came, and it sucked!  Really it sucked!  I made the biggest mistake of ordering Chicken Parmesan somewhere other than the Olive Garden.  It was not very good, the sauce was bad, and the chicken was very chewy.

My daughter, who loves burgers, didn't even eat her burger (it was well done, I made sure of that).

The service really sucks when there is a crowd, so if there is a wait for Houlihan's you are better off going elsewhere, possible across the street to Friday's or down the road to Chili's or the Olive Garden.

I've been there for lunch before and have had no complaints.  I wasn't impressed, but I was satisfied, not @ night!

Rosie's is one of those places you want to love.  It's bright and shiny and there is staff crawling all over the place.  A bakery case is always a welcome site at a breakfast place.

We were looking for competition for the world's best corned beef hash last sampled in Las Vegas.  The hash was house made and the poached eggs were well done but the seasoning was bland so the world record is still in Las Vegas. The Eggs Benedict were lukewarm on arrival.  Was the hotlamp not working?

A second trip the Huevos Rancheros beckoned.  One thing for sure, they don't do beans at Rosie's.  

After two trips including a second Sunday session with a regular church brunch group I'm sorry to say that the blush is a little off at Rosies'.  

Despite what looks like a lot of people, the kitchen is hopelessly slow.  It might have just been that we were there when the place was bustling but when the waiter comes back three times to refill the coffee before the breakfast shows up, he should be a little more insistent about getting some help from the kitchen.

Popularity and prime time is probably the cause of the slow service.  a good way to speed up turnover is to get the food out of the kitchen promptly.  Perhaps a little more practice will make perfect.

I dont eat seafood. I typically avoid, and deny any invites to it. 

But, i was in New Orleans, id be a fool to not be adventurous here.

Me and my friends found this spot randomly. It left such a great impression, we ate dinner here both nights that we stayed here. 

This place made me a difinitive lover of crawfish etouffee...thank you to your staffs patience and great hospitality.

And thank you for the introductiin to Abita Purple Haze!!!
They make an excellent flat white. It's a charming place, well decorated. The parking is a slight hassle, but that has more to do with the area than the coffeehouse.
Lots of awesome local artists and a great little outdoor art market. Def worth checking out.
The gravy cheese fries were SO delicious, but when I opened my hot dog there was a long black hair wrapped all in it... and I don't have black hair. Super grossed out, threw rest of the food away.

Sonobana surprised me in a good way for being located in a strip mall in West Nashville. 

I had some errands to do and figured I'd get some sushi to go. They told me it'd be 15-20 minutes for my order which was ready in the time frame that they gave me. When I stepped inside the restaurant I immediately noticed the traditional Japanese decor. It is nicely decorated and would be a good place to dine in. Service was quick and easy to pick up and pay.

Their menu is pretty big but I noticed that a lot of their rolls had a fried or partially fried element to it so I steered clear of those since I like raw rolls. I ordered a spicy tuna handroll, a yellow tail handroll and the Allison Roll which is just like a Philadelphia roll except it also has ahi tuna inside in addition to salmon, avocado and cream cheese. This totalled me about $18 which I'll admit is on the pricer side but the handrolls were actually bigger than I expected. I'd say my favorite of what I ordered was the yellowtail. It had green onion slices in it which went well with the flavor. 

Overall great experience!

I've only had a milkshake but oh my word it was good. Vegan pistachio milkshake was maybe the best shake I ever had. And the crayons, construction paper and markers at the table made us feel like kids.

This place was absolutely disgusting!  Please read the "not recommended review" by Mary S.  That review was 100% true.  Upon walking inside, it looked like an overcrowded airport terminal filled with nothing but students acting a fool.  Students dressed half naked with everything hanging out for all to see.  Not exactly what you want to see if you are looking for food.  The whole place was grimy feeling, like the place could have used a good cleaning.  Just trying to navigate through the place was like being in a maze!  There were hardly any signs and the signs that did exist were tiny and located near the ceiling at the end of the hallways!  Looking for a vending machine?  Good luck to you! We couldn't even find one and had to get something to drink out of an Uber eats kiosk!  What a joke!  Looking for a restroom?  Again, good luck to you and hopefully you don't wet your pants because you can't find one!  We walked in circles and found 2 restrooms in the whole place.  Forget the poor layout and trying to find signs or a directory of some sort...the amount of students standing in the way, walking slow as molasses, and just being plain obnoxious seeking attention from everyone was enough to make you go mad!  There was no way we wanted anything to eat from this place - just look at the kids preparing the food and then the atmosphere where you'd be stuck eating!  Absolutely not!
This place has amazing pizza and great service!! They really care here about the customers and their ingredients.

Wow what at a diamond in the rough! They have so many flavors you will definitely have a hard time deciding which one to get! I love the angel theme- strawberry angel wings in the popsicles, big beautiful angel wings on the wall you can take a picture with (coming back when I'm not in scrubs!) A cute place to take a date on a hot summer day. And the gentleman who helped me was extremely nice and explained each flavor and even said they are open to suggestions for future flavors. I got a churro sundae with mexican chocolate icecream (super yummy!!) coconut, whipped cream, chocolate and caramel sauces and and the churros were really soft and fluffy on the inside . I can't wait to return and try all of them!

This is a gorgeous monument.  I didn't know anything about Indy before we visited, so when we rounded the corner on our way to dinner and saw the monument, I gasped.  So much to look at, sculptures on every corner.  I wish the museum had been open.  I can see why so many people were hanging around on the steps, I would too.

The service we received was horrendous! I used to come often, and I can tell the service and quality of food has declined over time.  It took over an hour for our sushi, sashimi, and rolls to arrive.  To top it all off, they forgot to bring two of the rolls we ordered, and the rolls still showed up on the check.  I asked the hostess to remove the missing rolls and she said sorry, but it was an emotionless sorry, she really didnt' give a shit.  What a honey badger.  

The lady and her daughter who was sitting across from us was waiting for 20 minutes for a waitress to arrive.  No one came by.  She had to flag down someone twice before someone came to take her order.  I saw the frustration in her eyes and yes,it certainly was frustration because I had that same look in my eyes.

I was disappointed in the sushi rice.  Even I've made better sushi rice back home.  The rice was poorly seasoned and when I placed the piece of sushi in my mouth, I was greeted with a moist and mushy pad of rice.  What happened to the texture?  Either the rice was over cooked, or too much water was used to cook it. C'mon now, sushi rice is just as important as the cuts of fish.  Sushi 101 Fail. 

This place used to be good, just because it was busy didn't mean it could serve customers sloppy sushi and ignore them through the night.

Not worth coming back.

Hammock park to Dunedin is what Central Park is to NYC. Dunedin and Pinellas County is just a overpopulated City. However Hammock Park is an escape how Florida was decades ago. 
You would never know as you navigate the trails that the Gulf is just an 1/8 of a mile away. I have the sense of direction of a 90 year old snow birds first trip to the south but have never got lost on the trails.  The key is to remember what trail you came in on as they almost all lead several of the main ones and branch off. 
This park is what shows when a community pulls together. It is not a state park but a city park however without the community this park would be invaded by plant species that would ruin it. 
The cleanliness of the park is like not other. The signange for trails and information is immaculate.
