There is a frisbee golf course, hiking trails, plenty of benches on those trails, pavilions with picnic tables, playgrounds and quite a few parking lots.

The decor was pretty much like a Denny's or Bob Evans, which I didn't mind.  The service was good. One would think that since this is a pancake place, the pancakes would shine; however, they were disgusting! The biscuits and gravy were flavorless. The coffee was burnt as well. An overall horrible Saturday brunch.

I'm really surprised at these reviews! If you've ever been to Wasabi on 82nd or Sushi Bar in Broad Ripple, you'll never go to this place twice. The sushi was disappointing to say the least. I frequent sushi bars in the Indy area, and was excited to try this location. Not worth it, even at half price. The rolls were small and didn't taste fresh. The only time I have ever left sushi on my plates untouched! The good: The restaurant was really trendy inside, and the cocktails were good...only reason for 2 stars instead of 1! I'd go back for a drink, but not the sushi.

I stupidly got a mailbox without checking reviews. This is the rudest place I've EVER been to for post offices in my entire life. They take forever to process your stuff and they're expensive $60 for two months??? This would be ok if it was a nice sweet place but ummmn no it's not! 
The main guy that works there (you'll know when you see him he's a obvious character) thinks he's all that and snaps at customers and literally walks around like he is mad at the world.
 If you ask him a question he ignores you if most of the time and if you ask again he rudely sighs like he doesn't want to help. 

I'm really nice and kind and no matter what HES RUde RUDE RUde. I asked how he was doing when I first started coming and every time he would ignore me..... The last straw was when I went to get my packages that were lying RIGHT THERE and he said I had to wait 45 min wTF!!!!! 

Um I have a life look up the packages numbers and simply give me my stuff! But no I have to wait until they put a f ing slip in my mailbox !!!!????? Which a many times they have not and I had to wait.....when my two months are up I'll be relocating to a place that isn't so f ing rude 
Leave your personal issues at home and if you hate your job don't work there!

If there was a time to yelp a place before going, it would be before going to Monell's. while in town for business, everyone and their mother had told us to go to Monell's but no one had told us the concept and AMOUNT OF FOOD THAT KEEPS COMING AND COMING.

Though it was a surprise to us, I loved the family cooking and sitting vibe.  We got there late on a Tuesday night, so there was a table open for the 4 of us, some random tourists later joined us. 

There's no menu here. They just bring out bowls of EVERYTHING they make for the night. They told us this after thy had brought out the corn bread and biscuits. Again, had I known this from doing my research on yelp, I would have skipped the bread...though I don't think that would have saved me from the glorious food coma I was in later.

Next came the hot food: fried chicken (one of the best ever), veggie lasagna (could have skipped this), beef stew (the best I've had), mashed potatoes, green beans, their famous corn pudding, cannelini beans and turnips. I tell ya, I was in heaven and in pain at the same time. Amazing. Delicious. Real southern home cooking, at its best.

After this was dessert, which for the night I was there was peach cobbler. Can't comment on it personally as I didn't have room to try it. My coworkers seemed impressed with it.

Skip meals all day and save the room for this. You won't regret it.

Very good food, found on yelp, passing thru Nashville wanting lunch just outside of city. Would recommend again. Good location rt off hwy, 1/2 hr sit down lunch. Salsa, chips, guac, tacos, chimichanga all delish

Went for a holiday luncheon. Loved the bell on a ribbon we received when we came in. They food was Meh. Nothing stands out but the crabmeat cheesecake. Have had something similar at Jacque-Imo's. We set the water on the floor because there was not room on the table. The server knocked it over on accident. Maybe my fault for putting it down there. Thought it was out of the way. The bottle was almost empty so the spill was very small. She then came back in the middle of the lunch and asked my co worker to stand up and move out of her way so she could mop.  Hmmmmm. 
It was beautifully decorated for the holidays. All in all not impressed.

Had a GREAT experience with the service department at Suntrup Kia South County! Special thank you to Brian Richter for helping me with my car problems and giving me his honest feedback on the issue at hand. You were great to work with and I will definitely be coming back!

It's rare to find Japanese curry in a restaurant. Sushi Shoya's is authentic and tasty! The Gyoza had perfect seasoning. We shared a specially roll and sushi combo - awesome. Unlike many restaurants that serve Japanese food that's passable, this chef is Japanese raised and it shows! Also, the restaurant is clean, charming and so Japanese. Best sushi in Pinellas county.

What an adorable spot for brunch! Right in the middle of State St. this is in the La Arcada plaza which also has super cute stores to explore while you're here. We came on a Saturday at about 1pm and it was not crowded at all. We were seated right away at a table in the outside seating area which was exactly what I had hoped for so that we could enjoy the beautiful Santa Barbara weather. 

-Fig burger - Holy smokes, this was totally delicious!! 5 stars for this! I really wanted to try something with fig given the name of the restaurant so I opted for the burger. There was the perfect amount of fig jam spread on the bun such that I tasted the hint of sweetness in every bite but that it didn't overpower the burger. The bacon and caramelized onions also added a lot to the burger! Of note, I opted to get the burger without the bleu cheese as it's not really my favorite cheese. 

-Short rib benedict - Exactly what I imagined. Short rib was tasty, soft, and tender. I thought that there was too much hollandaise for me drenched over the benedict and that it was quite oily but all in all, still enjoyed it. The poached eggs were perfect. Home fries on the side was not crispy enough on the outside nor seasoned enough which I was sad about. 3.5 stars for this dish and not sure if it's worth the $18.5. 

I will most definitely want to return here and try some other dishes if I get a chance to come back to Santa Barbara!

We were a group of 4 college mates that gathered here for dinner.  We did not have a reservation, so they made us wait outside for nearly 25 minutes.  They only have tables inside.  The food is pricey, but quality seems to be good.  We had grilled paneer and Baingan Bhartha with garlic naan and it was great.

We found mostly non-Indian clents seated in the restaurant, which to me is a good sign.  The food here seems to appeal to all of them.

Give it a try if you want to taste Indian food, especially for the first time.

Visiting from out of town, and a friend recommended Salon Bravo at 425 Cleveland Street (I notice this page says 649 Cleveland so I'm not sure if it's the same business). Happy to say I would recommend it too! 
Very happy with my visit to this salon! Went in for a color touch up, trim, and style, and Sally did an amazing job! The color match was perfect, and the product she used didn't leave my hair with any chemical scent. Also, the way my hair was trimmed and styled made it look better than it has looked in a very long time! Thank you Sally!

Speedy take out service with great options. The staff is super friendly and helpful. I even left my debit card their once and the owner reached out to me to make sure I got it back. What a great team!

This little place is tucked into the Petsmart/Trader Joe's shopping center but don't underestimate it!
The space is open and well-lit with natural light during the day. The kitchen is directly behind the bar as are two very large flat screens. 
They have a slew of genuinely good beers and an attentive and informed staff to bring them to you. 
We tried the Monsoon Dunkel, Salida del Sol Amber, 1811 Desert Blonde, and the sour. Each was flavorful and VERY drinkable. 
I highly recommend stopping into this brewery and picking out a flight.

Have been there twice. On the first visit I was fortunate enough to try their Breakfast Porter (exquisite and blew the rest of their dark offerings away) as well as the first pour from their Banc Vert saison keg (another delicious beer). Neither were on offer the second time around, so settled for the coffee stout, which was enjoyable but nothing to write home about, like Cycle's Cream and Sugar, Please. Place was quite busy on a Sunday afternoon. Great location, great latin food next door. Friendly and helpful staff.

The male customer rep is horrible doesnt even know his own policies. The car I rented was filthy n had no gas cap with a 3k mile drive that's upsetting didnt realize until I was in Virginia in country so I was screwed.  Windshield wipers were crap and had to stay in car part on side road for 12 hrs due to snowing in Tennessee cause wipers didnt work on my 2019 ford explorer . For 6 days they decided to charge me 1,100 dollars I make this trip with enterprise 380 for 7 days same car . Never ever again do not go there they will screw u . And now cant get a customer rep to help .

The chicken maroosh from here is my go-to whenever I am in this area. I love how savory the chicken is, with fresh vegetables and a delicious sauce to top it off. After going to Saad's I always go next door to Manakeesh Bakery for some baklava.
fast check out...you can find all your grocery needs...friendly staff...reasonable prices...why not shop here
An amazing vibe with great service. I ordered a boba milk tea and definitely wasn't disappointed. The staff went out of their way to make sure I had an amazing experience. Thank you!
I love it here. The staff is so friendly, there is an upstairs and downstairs and always a good crowd. Beers aren't over priced. Definitely a good place for sitting at a bar or dancing.

Food is 4 stars but service and respect is a 0. I was a very loyal customer for months probably going atleast once a week. Came in for pickup and the man at the front desk accused me repeatedly that I did not give a tip on a meal during dine in. After explaining to him I did not have dinner with a party of 4 he kept asking me why I didn't tip. Very rude and I never returned again.

$22.95 AYCE Dinner 3pm - 9:30pm 7 days a week. We came in on Sunday evening at 5pm, and baked mussels (which are creamy and delicious) included in the all you can eat, as well as 3 or 4 items from their appetizer menu. The chef was very attentive, as was the server. We never were kept waiting there at the bar, although it was pretty empty. All of the fish tasted fresh, and they have a big selection of rolls to choose from. 

There are a couple of big tv's there with the NBA Finals playing. The place began to fill up as we were leaving. I was hesitant to come here, as my experience in this same building back when it used to be Sushi 7 was very disappointing. 

The chef asked if we wanted to try the sea urchin. Well we did, I am not a fan at all!! It's a brownish colour with the consistency of yogurt, and it tasted like what you might scoop out of the bottom of a fish tank. Actually it tasted like the ocaen, but super strong. It's a very pungent flavour that stay with you. Try it if you dare!! I thought it was cool that he offered us something unusual though. 

Try the:

Kitzmo Godzilla (Deep Fried) - Cream cheese, godzilla roll with spicy crab on top, habanero sauce, teriyaki sauce

Double Crunch - Tempura shrimp, cream cheese, avocado, tempura flakes, sweet mayo, teriyaki sauce

Picoso (Deep fried) - Tempura shrimp, crab, cream cheese, jalapeno, cilantro, habanero, teriyaki sauce

Diamond - Spicy crab, cucumber, albacore, yellow tail, avocado, tobiko, teriyaki sauce

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Didn't like:

Gyoza Sake - Fried potstickers, salmon, lemon slice, avocado, spicy crab

Sea urchin nigiri - YUCK!
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Happy eating!

I LOVE Primo Hoagies, fresh quality meats, cheeses and veggies and they use Liscio's wonderful, sesame seed topped freshly baked rolls, truly the best rolls money can buy! 

They offer a wide array of hoagie combo's and wraps, plus whole pickles, macaroni, potato or tortellini salads and cole slaw, hot pepper shooters, fresh mozzarella, chips, pretzels and a stand up cooler full of ice cold drinks. 

This location is the most convenient to my home, literally a few minutes drive, however, I do drive to the next town over or the next after trying this location before. 

Today was my second try, they are just so cheap with the meat! Other Primo's pack it in, here you almost feel like you are eating a ham and cheese salad on a roll. 

I ordered the Primo ( the mid sized hoagie, as they come in three sizes ). Tavern ham and Swiss cheese, but please add salami and provolone as well. No problem, well maybe not for them, but for me, paying extra for one tissue thin layer of hard salami and I do mean one tissue thin layer well spread out and never over lapping and another of the provolone, what gives with that and the ends of both sides of the hoagie had no ham in it! 

Stop being so cheap, I say to the young dark haired man that made my sandwich, I'll keep driving to the next town over.

They are definitely a dive bar to the fullest!

I find their mixed drinks are a little pricier than most dive bars and I do t get the logic behind that. If you are a dive bar be a dive bar all the way around. 

The atmosphere on a Friday is a mixed generational crowd. I think the only reason it may attract youngins is due to location it's walkable from many neighborhoods - main reason we went. 

The food is typical bar food which is good. But just order fried foods because deli foods come from the attached deli next door and they suck. 

The place could also use a very deep cleansing and cleaning.

Really fresh ingredients, and I love how you can fill up your bowl with plenty of different meats, seafood, and veggies as well as a large assortment of spices and sauces. A great bang for you buck. Clean and friendly too.

Not going to go into too much detail, but this place charged me and my friends way more than they advised that it would be and my polish was cracking within less than 2 days. Save your money for a better salon.

Unfortunately, my experience was not like the others below. This place is very small about ten tables, which is fine but how long we had to wait for our eggs and French toast doesn't add up. This is a buffet breakfast with unlimited mimosas. We were told that the mimosas would be brought to our table. We got our food and sat down, 30 minutes later... still no mimosas, still no eggs that they said would also be brought to our table. We had to go in to get our own mimosas. We asked one of the waitresses about the status of our order and she literally rolled her eyes at us and started walking away. An hour and a half later, I go to the counter for the sixth time to state I haven't gotten my eggs or French toast and requested a refund. Throughout all of that time that I was there, new people sat down next to us and got their eggs and other items delivered to their table. I'd like to mention that we were there before many of this people. So after an hour and a half, all I had at this establishment was there buffet, which also was barely stocked. I do not recommend this place.

So color me surprised this place cen is actually pretty good. We had a big group so it was difficult to get a reservation at other brunch places and also not have to get super early to go at opening. 

Super nice decor. I thought it would be more doner like but it was super nice all around. 

We got a mix of brunch, lunch stuff from the salmon hash, omelettes, lox bagel plate, Belgian waffles, to the rad na, lobster Mac and cheese,and the French onion soup dumplings.

Everything was good, not mind blowing, but good honest food.  

We were surprised by the diversity and range of the food so that was a plus. 

So yeah will definitely come back if we have this kind of need again.

Very nice on initial phone call.  Despite spending time on phone and in-person review, quote was not as discussed and multiple emails requesting clarification/correction resulted in zero reply.  Guess my job wasn't big enough to bother even communicating.   Would not recommend as follow up in quoting process was not good.   Would it really be too much to just tell me my job was too small/far/something?

My favorite place for Mexican food (especially seafood) when I'm in the area.  They have an excellent selection of  Mexican refrescos and of course the Coke made with sugar instead of that other crap.  THEY ALSO HAVE VEG OPTIONS! They used to not have sweet tea but recently started carrying it.  I had the spice pork tacos and a seafood mix tostado with tea for under $10.   The tacos are 99cents and are a bit smaller than most Americanized versions you are probably used to so order 1 or 2 more than you think you can eat.  The spicy pork was delicious, well flavored and with enough meat and other toppings to make them adequate, they will come on corn tortillas so if you want other, specify!  I have had several of they seafood tostados and they are freakin huge!  You actually get another bare tostado to move some of the toppings onto and you'll need it.  Service is great and even when packed usually don't have to wait long for my food.

Wow! This place needs a lot of work! Not sure if their brunch is a weekly thing but they ought to give up and throw in the towel on it.
We had a reservation for their 11:30 seating. Once we were finally seated, after waiting 10 minutes watching others in *after us* be seated, our OJ and coffee were brought. 
The OJ was served in a plastic cup. The coffees were lukewarm. We sent them back and It then took another ten minutes for hot coffee.
We ordered the "chicken 'n waffles" ($18). Ugh! Once we got our food, FORTY-FIVE MINUTES LATER, the waffles were way underdone. A waffle should at least be golden brown. They were barely brown and soft and flimsy.
Needless to say, I cannot honestly say we enjoyed the experience. The two chicken fingers on the plate weren't bad, actually. But, a half cooked waffle with no butter and about 2 oz of syrup left A LOT to be desired.
Once we left I ended up being in a mood that I just spent $36.00 plus tax and tip -- yelling to our friends within our party in conversation because the music was so loud and being hungry an hour later. They had a band that would normally be nice "in the background" for a brunch! Not these guys! It was as loud as midnight on a Saturday night!
All in all...a big bust of an experience! Definitely won't waste my money at this place.

A truly extraordinary meal and experience...something I will not forget! I had the Tasting Menu for dinner, along with my partner. The Baba Gahnnouj was a particular stand-out on the Mezza Platter, but everything was flavorful and a perfect compliment to our entrees. Would highly recommend the "Mixed Grill for One" as it gives you a terrific smattering. I loved the Shish Taouk and Kafta, and the potatoes were seasoned to perfection. 

To top it all off, for dessert we had the Ghazal Beirut (I've never been a cotton candy fan, but this dish was life altering on that front), the Mammould Mad, and an on-the-house Kanafe Cheese. Finished the meal very full, with leftovers a plenty, and deeply happy.

Antoine ("Tony") runs the restaurant with his family and serves as the primary server/host. A wonderful and warm man whose joy was contagious and blended with the atmosphere. He reminded me of a favorite Uncle! I left Li Beirut giving Tony a hug and being treated like a long lost relative. My kind of place. The music, from what I could tell, was a mix of Lebanese pop and more traditional sounds. Really gave the restaurant some pep, zing, and pop.

I'll absolutely be returning to Li Beirut for the high-quality food, and the warm environment!

I love chicken, always have. Even during the 90s aka the golden age of pizza slices I stayed firm in my commitment to chicken. Then about three years ago I began researching the source of conventional chicken and the affects of hormone and antibiotic treatment. The deeper I dug the worse it got. I felt like JLC (Jamie Lee Curtis) in True Lies, everything I thought I knew and loved had been a dirty violent sham. 

Since becoming neurotic about my chicken it's been very difficult to stop somewhere and get some clean healthy chicken to eat on the run. I read about Rotisseur when they first opened and I saw that they use Pennsylvania chickens but I couldn't find if they were cage free and untreated. 

Today I forgot my lunch and there was only one thing I wanted and you know I ain't talkin' about falafel. I figured I'd look at Pure Fare and maybe Honeygrow, but in the back of my mind I was thinking man I wish Rotisseur was good to go. Decided to pull up the menu and bam, all natural, antibiotic, cage, and hormone free Amish chicken. It was the answer to my prayers (and clearly printed on the menu).

Cruised on over, ordered a half chicken, it was ready in like five if that. Got some cups of hot sauce and was back at my desk, 15 minutes round trip. I usually salt the ish out of my chicken but this was brined to perfection and oozed natural flavored goodness. No salt needed and I only used about a quarter of the hot sauce. The sides look phenomenal as well but I was really just testing the waters today but there is no doubt I'll be back soon.

This will sound dumb, but it might have been the best salad I have ever had.  Simple blackened Shrimp Salad with homemade Green Goddess Dressing.  If they do everything as well as they do salad, the rest of the menu must be amazing.  

Waitress was a little gruff, but it went with the style of the bar.  

FYI, no one under 21 is allowed in this place.

We had Kim, aka Angel and she was AWESOME.  We had so much fun, she told us all the ghost stories about the different buildings.  Educational and entertaining--she was so knowledgeable.  After the tour she gave us some recommendations on great places for dining and cocktails.  She made it a great experience!

This is the second time in a few months I've gotten roast pork with spinach, sharp provolone and raw onions. I used to go to 10 the and Oregon until they closed up. I can't understand why you would make spinach so spicy hot. The amount of heat just kills the taste of the spinach and actually takes away from the roast pork. Maybe the taste buds of whoever Cooks it are fried? It's just not enjoyable to sweat from eating spinach. Maybe someone who works there will read this but it's too late for me. I will have to find another place for my roast pork.
Every time I come to this establishment I can always expect great, cleanliness and friendly service. The sushi is on point along with other variety dishes on their menu.

I went in for happy hour and have to say, it's pretty legit! Got there a little after 5 pm on a Thursday and had no problem finding seating. Booths are pretty limited but the chairs were fairly comfortable. Happy hour consists of half off drinks AND appetizers. This makes me happy because so many places cheese out on their happy hour offerings by only taking a dollar off...if I'm happy with your happy hour, I'll come back at other hours too!

My friend and I had the malbec (there were two, we went the cheap route) and it was decent. Worth $3.50 a pour easily. The food was also pretty tasty. The pretzel was GIANT, warm, and covered in salt...a little too much for my liking, but it was easy to scrape off. What got me all tied up in knots about this dish was the 'beer cheese' for dipping. Let me just warn you - do not expect some kind of ooey, gooey cheese. This stuff was dry and very difficult to spread. The odd taste and funky texture did not enhance the pretzel in any way. It was almost reminiscent of space food...if I was on an interstellar journey and not in Boise, I would have probably enjoyed it. However, I opted to just eat my salty pretzel without it. We also got the onion petals and my mind instantly thought of a blooming onion esque dish. What came out were what could really be described as petals - an overflowing dish of thick onion slices, perfectly coated in batter and deep fried. This made such a huge difference because every piece tasted delicious. The accompanying dipping sauce (I think it was ranch) really worked. We ate the whole plate!!

I will say, I was disappointed in the service. When we first got there, things were not super busy, the restaurant was halfway full. Our waitress did not seem to be entertained from the moment she stopped by our table. Maybe my opening with a SELF deprecating joke was the wrong choice. Usually if I go out, I like to lighten the mood to begin with so the wait staff knows my table is easygoing and they are free to joke with us too! Not the case here. This girl seemed like she wanted to avoid our table at any cost, and in fact, she was successful in doing so. It easily took her 20-25 minutes to check on us after bringing out the food, only to ask if we wanted more drinks. Well, if she had checked 10 minutes prior and it was still happy hour, yes, we had planned on getting another round of drinks. But the fact that negligence on her part resulted in it being past that time, we did not feel it justifiable to pay the full price. Instead we just said we would like some ice waters (no, it was never offered to begin with). When she came back with the waters, she slammed them down. I thought maybe I was just imagining things, but my friend even turned to me and was shocked at how rude a gesture that was. If it was an accident, I would think the waitress would have apologized for making so  much noise. Instead she just turned on her heel.

All in all, this place is pretty cool and the owners really opened it up. It's a lot more lively than Table Rock was, although I do miss the giant Hopzilla cutout. I'm really excited to come back and try their veggie burger and fries (they had so many options that all sounded AMAZING). Not to mention all of the different sauces! As long as the joke police isn't my server next time, I'm sure my rating could definitely improve.

I used to be a person who loves pizza but hates salad. My friends recomended the poke bowl salad to me. I loves this salad immediately! Next day, I ordered meatzza pizza. It tastes good as well. This new restaurant is close to school building, so we have a new place for quick meal.

this is some serious southern cajun NOLA style food.

the beignets are little fluffy sugary pillows of heavenly warm dough! come here for these yumms on wednesday and sunday, the only days they serve them.

hidden in the middle of the bustle of reading terminal, this is a great fast, different foodery.

There are a basic set of car wash standards that every auto wash should meet.  That includes cleaning your wheels. For what ever reason, this car wash is incapable of performing that basic task on my BMW 335i. I had to finish the job when  I got home. I'm not looking for perfection, but their performance severely lacked in that regard. 

Besides that, the rest of the car was adequately cleaned.  I will not be a repeat customer.

Thank you,  Precision,  for doing a wonderful job with my two cars.
(I hit one with the other..)
You were kind, friendly and went the "extra mile" to fix my damaged car. What a surprise !
The person in charge of my case was Gabriel - who made things easy
and fast. And when I needed a ride, he quickly set up a driver for me.
I met China and Tony who were a pleasure and both special people.
I would trust Precision anytime and felt the whole experience was 5 Star  !

So..... Margaritas and the appetizer was good..... But the tacos we're not that impressive sadly. We could've made a home made taco from Hello fresh better than that... 
Side note.... The 2 pineapple margaritas taste way different than each other

Based on management's response to my review, I am reaffirming my three-star review and elaborate further here. 

1) the ice cream was "tasty" and enjoyable. I didn't find it creamy. As I said in my previous review, it am more of a traditionalist when it comes to ice cream, and Scoop won't be on my list of choices in the future. If in Center City Franklin Fountain, Big Gay, or Bassett's would be my first choice. Outside of Center City I'd choose Handel's, Weckerly's, or Little Baby's. Lots of other places come to choose from, but these are some of my favorite. 

2) I didn't appreciate the colors of the ice cream. Personal preference for sure, but they were bright and unappealing to me. Again, personal preference. 

3) I don't remember a chocolate flavor among the options!

4) Again, totally my preference, but I didn't care for the menu (it was overwhelming to me). For example, the manager said in their feedback to my first review that I could have ordered a scoop. While it may have been an option, it didn't seem like the kind of place where one just got a scoop and the menu clearly didn't lead me to that choice. 

5) The staff was certainly friendly. 

6) I stand behind my three-rating. Others may very much disagree with me, and I can very much appreciate that. This is my informed opinion.

Best ciders I've ever had. Worst service I've ever had. Ignored by the bartender for 20 minutes then waited in line instead to order flights and was shoved paper to write down what we wanted and told "I'll do it when you're ready"...we WERE ready. We had what we wanted picked out for 20 minutes. We came here with full intentions of buying a few cases and some merch to support this company but we will not be back. Seriously disappointed. No sense of urgency or customer service here.
The place is gone. The Grand Sierra Resort  is remodeling and I believe Johnny Rockets might be moved downstairs. Will keep posted.

This place was surprisingly good.  It's a mishmash of Italian and French inspired sandwiches and crepes.  The crepes were great -- not too sweet, which seems to be a common pitfall of American made crepes.  

The pesto sandwich with mozzarella was good as well.

This is one of my go-to coffee shops and one of my absolute favorite places! They have a wide selection of drinks as well as food (and great breakfast sandwiches), so there's something for everyone. 

What I like most about this place is that it is open late (until 10pm) whereas most coffee shops close around 6 or 7, which is too soon after work to get anything done. I also like that it is a large cafe with lots of tables. I have never had an issue finding a place to sit, which is often not the case because cafes in the city are very small. 

This place has an overall great vibe and it is always full of people studying, having meetings and getting work done. I come here when I need to spread myself out and log in a few hours of work, whether personally or professionally. 

If you haven't been yet, then what are you waiting for?!

The fact that people eat here makes my stomach turn.  The place is filthy.   The bathrooms smell like a homeless camp without plumbing.   You cook your own steak and everything else is fried.   The bar is the only decent thing here.   If you like to cook your own food in a port a potty then please go.

Ordered and paid $$$ for overnight delivery so I could take it with me on a business trip. I even had a couple of days extra to spare just in case. Called the next afternoon and find out they shipped it ground! Of course it arrived while I was out of state at my event. They have dickered about the refund, return shipping costs, etc....over THEIR MISTAKE. They made it all my problem and now are holding tight to their website declaration that they have 15 business days to provide a refund. No apology, no "we'll take care of it" attitude, don't worry we will make you whole and then some. Instead they first blamed me for not calling sooner, and now for disputing the charge on my credit card. SOS as far as I can tell. You have been forewarned!

We were a party of 4 from this past Friday night. Our food was good, steak was cooked correctly. Our service was really good! Jazzy was on it...fast, efficient, and a fun personality too. She really added to an overall great meal!

Pretty traditional Mexican fare-it was good but not spectacular. The portions are good size. The outside patio is pleasant, and the service was good. It is super convenient, and there is plenty of parking close by. A nice place to stop in on State Street.

I accidentally left the dresses my wife wanted to bring to Tampa for the weekend at home. So, we needed dresses for when we went out to dinner at the places I had made reservations. Fortunately, I know my wife loves dresses by Torrid and found one in a mall not far from the meadery were going to pay a visit. 

Located at the Citrus Park Mall, Torrid was easy to locate from the northside entrance by Dick's. I picked up for my wife a couple of nice dresses she saw and some other items. 

Overall the experience was quite nice, being I've never set foot in a Torrid before. The sales associates were very friendly. We found what we needed for the weekend, and all was right in the universe.

What can I say that hasn't already been said? Food is filling and the location is convenient. The servers there were nice, albiet the service was a bit slow when we came. 

Got the stead for 10 bucks which was a good deal and the bacon patty melt was solid. 

For the price, you can't beat having a great hot meal. Its not the cleanest and its not the nicest place, but you go there to get some quick hot food.

Came in fairly late on a Friday night to grab dinner with my husband. Restaurant looked clean and the layout is great. We got ourselves a booth that has its own tv that you can change the channel yourself and the volume. That is defiantly great. A few minutes late our waitress showed up and got us a couple of 25 oz beers and dropped off the menus. Pretty basic sports bar food burgers, sandwiches ect. We ordered the finger steaks for a appetizer and didn't have to wait to long. They where fresh and good also a decent amount. My husband ordered the Ghost Burger and had them add Bacon and I ordered the mushroom burger. We got the food in the average amount of time and it was super hot and fresh. The Garlic Frys are amazing and my husband said the Ghost burger was great if you like spicy. My burger however was very over cooked, there where very few mushrooms on it and they are not kidding when they say charbroil as all I could taste was burnt meat. Needless to say I did not finish it. My husband gave me his Bacon to cheer me up and it was by far the best part of my meal. Service was great and our  waitress was very friendly and accommodating. May stop in for a appetizer and drink to watch a game but didn't feel the food was worth the money.

Always loved Rosa's 
Good pizza, good cause, good people.
This little shop is adorable with all the post it notes everywhere. Also have had some new ordering stations.
Great salon! I was able to make an appointment on the same day I called and I am very happy with my cut from Holly.

When I was in high school, my friends and I would 'sneak' downtown and hang out here as much as we could.  This place just made us feel so cool for some reason and I laugh thinking about how we would order coffees and try to act all hip and haughty.  We must've looked painfully obvious, but at the time it was such a thrill.  That being said, I still loved visiting J J's when I moved back to Nashville for college and still do today.  

Although it is no longer a regular haunt of mine, I still enjoy stopping in here from time to time.  J J's is such a unique place, there is nothing like it in Nashville.  It is labeled as a Market and from the outside, looks to be just that.  The exterior is that of a boring, typical corner store and tricks you into thinking it'll hold the regular types of market merchandise, ramen and toilet paper and other generic products household products.  But entering J J's you find a much more tasteful and exciting selection of domestic and imported wares.  There's a large stock of higher end chocolates, in more varieties than you would expect.  They sell a surprisingly good selection of teas (lots of loose leaf yum) and coffees, some local, some not.  And an eclectic mish-mash of higher end grocery items.  Now granted J J's is small so their collection is not too incredibly extensive, but it's a great place to stop and pick up some odds and ends on the way home.    They also have a decent selection of cold beer, a lot of nicer breweries you can't find in your typical corner market and the sell kegs as well.  

What sets JJ's apart from other places isn't their amazing taste in merchandise, it's the atmosphere.  The market is only half of what makes up this place, my favorite part of JJ's is their 'lounge' area.  If you walk past the front counter you enter the back room which is a cozy little area filled with worn in chairs and tables.  On this side of the store, the front counter is turned into a coffee bar, where you can order a delicious version of your favorite coffee drink.  The 'lounge' is stocked with battered board games and reading material, and spending time here feels more like hanging out at a friends house than a local business.  I love meeting up with a couple friends here, grabbing a coffee and relaxing, playing one of their games or just chit chatting quietly.

The staff here are some of the friendliest in town and are always ready to help in anyway they can.  The prices are a little high but not more than expected as most of their merchandise can be hard to find anywhere else in town.  Their location on the Vanderbilt side of Broadway is in very convenient walking distance to a lot of hotels if you're a visitor, dorm rooms if you're a student, and lots of local businesses including music row, if you're looking for a spot to stop for a coffee break or an informal meeting.  This convenient walking location also means it can be a terrible parking location.  Spaces are extremely limited close by and on busy times of the day, you will probably spend more time looking for a spot than you will drinking your coffee.

Tasty sandwiches right on Whyte - good alternative for when you don't want to actually hit a sit-down place for lunch.  Lots of room inside to sit, or take it to go.
Sandwiches are quite tasty (though they lose one star for committing the ultimate sin of putting mayonnaise on my sandwich after specifically asking for none....YUCK!!!) and the soup is pretty good (but best enjoyed on location - doesn't travel well).

The food is average at best but most of the time the service is great. really nice and friendly guys and girls working there. you can tell they try the best with what they have at their disposal but the rolls and lunch meat arent the best out there. there are better places in the neighborhood to go to if you want a good hoagie or steak. their wings are pretty dang good though. i wont go there too often for reasons i mentioned above but once in a while ill have a craving for their wings or buffalo chicken cheesesteak and im always treated well by the staff.
2nd and last... look it's nice but damn the food isn't cutting it.. this lobster tail was overcooked and $135 for this tomahawk was subpar. I'm not sure I follow the hype?

Went here last night with a couple of co workers. We went for the crawfish boil but when we saw they were $16 a lb we changed our mind and ordered dishes off the menu which was reasonable. I had the crawfish pie and it was fantastic. We also had an order of the gumbo poutine and it was out of this world. Will definitely come back next time in town

Not bad by any means but not great either...the general consensus of the food and experience was meh.

   We started with beers all around (once we were finally helped), I had their blueberry cobbler and I believe someone else had a sour. Also ordered the Mac n cheese and cornbread for the table, Mac was ok but the corn bread was to die for! I believe had we ordered the pulled pork Mac it would have been out of this world.
   Since I checked in on Yelp, I was to receive their pork belly sample but they were out so she brought brisket samples out for the whole table which was thoughtful. Slightly dry but the sauce took care or that.

   For our meals:
      Pulled pork with tangy sauce and baked beans
      Pulled pork sandwich

The pork was pretty dry, the sauce comes on the side which I like and the tangy sauce is something else! However, I feel that pork is one of those meats gat should never be dry.

All in all, decent BBQ but I don't think I'd be back a second time.
Too Christiany.... Continuously bombarded by ads for local churches and movies and ads for Jesus. It's like The Lord hired them to be their promotions company. Truly obnoxious....

First time visiting this place.  Didn't look at Yelp reviews before going in, but can now see why people talk about how bad customer service.  Customer service couldn't have been worse.  As first timers, we didn't realize that you had to order at kiosks.  No more than 6 people eating at the time when we entered.  Not one employee even looked at us while we waited at the counter.  Than we saw someone else come in and realized that you order from kiosks.  Person delivered the food on a tray and literally dropped on the table and left.   Never said a word to us like enjoy your meal, etc.  food was pricy for what you get.  I think Bryn or Dave may want to spend some time at this location, because it's obvious that there is a morale problem or maybe someone is forcing the people to work here.  Can't say I've been to many places where staff was any more rude than here.  Good luck! Won't be back.

Probably one of the best restaurants I've ever been to. Not to take that statement lightly. 

Going here in the summer is the absolute best, their outdoor seating is top notch. I went here on a whim, got a bar seat outside by the patio type bar and was greeted with friendly conversation from the bartender, who was more than interested in helping me decide what to order and what to drink. I ordered a ton, and every single thing I ordered was phenomenal. I couldn't help but text my friends and family while I was sitting at the bar to tell them about how good it was. 

I took my family here shortly after that and was seated outside by that patio again, this time at night and it was so beautiful. They set up the outside with cute overhead lighting and it makes for an awesome ambience. Once again, food and drinks were incredible. I can't say I specifically remember what I got, but now having been there a few times, I have never ever been misled and have never walked away anything but blown away, waiting to come back again.

This place is the definition of RATCHET, but I still had a helluva good time. Why? I stumbled into here drunk and forced my fiance to dance with me for hours. The drinks were pretty expensive, but really strong. Great fuel for the AWESOME music: house, EDM, top 40, and 90s hip hop.  Really something for everybody! And when we were taking breaks from the AIR-CONDITIONED dance floor, we people watched and saw some really, really amusing/disgusting/funny sights. I do not miss being young and single.

My recommendation: Get drunk elsewhere and come here to keep your buzz going and dance up a storm!

It's been a minute since I got to hang at Pignic but I had a plan last Saturday and this was part of the party! 

Pignic was part of the Out & About Pride Party and they concocted a sweet and tart cocktail that sounded super interesting. They called it the Rainbow Sure-bet, a little play on words that brought the biggest little city and the flavor of the drink, which tasted like that classic non-dairy frozen treat!

The drink was colorful and well balanced, plus garnished with some rainbow fun. They used 10 Torr vodka and infused it with rainbow sour candy for the base, then mixed it with some blood orange and bartender magic, and viola, delicious. 

The bartender was very quick with the cocktails and super efficient too. There weren't really too many patrons around when we stopped in, but dang she was fast and every drink came out the same, just as it should. 

Very impressive all around.

I like to make burgers. When I make burgers I like to season the meat, then add toppings. This place forgets about the meat and lets you pick from a slew of toppings. The end result is that you get a slab of tasteless meat with some really awesome toppings. And that is THE only draw of this place for me. 

Besides the many many toppings, they also have many many varieties and flavors for sodas and milkshakes.

Oh and the onion rings were good.

HOW CAN YOU SERVE UNSEASONED MEAT!

Great sports bar. Plenty of TVs. If you don't see the game you're looking for, ask. The service was great on a busy Saturday night downtown NOLA. Terry our server, and Evelyn, the manager, were great! We tried two appetizers that were tasty and fast. Good beer selection, too

This place told me they could do a mani pedi and I waited for 40 minutes, my nails completely chipped off after 2 days and I got an infection on my toe where they cut my skin by accident! Gross don't go.

STAY AWAY!!!!  1 star just so i can add a post. This experience was so terrible its hard to put in words. I literally feel anxiety when i think of it. I will not go into it in full detail because it's very frustrating, but the lack of customer service and general knowledge of their merchandise being delivered is incomprehensible. Nobody knows what's delivered and when, then when you want a refund they don't have record of the delivery team picking up the still boxed furniture they already picked up. Lots of hours and multiple days wasted on this company only to still not get what we paid for. NEVER EVER AGAIN.

Another fabulous find for our bookclub forays =)

I almost completely walked by the cafe huddled under my umbrella last night, tucked into a quiet corner shop in the midst of the neon and noise of the Italian market. Inside is a little bit of a mix of your grandmom's living room and attic. The couches are well worn in, the fireplace was sadly fake, and if you're ever not sure which country the owner's from just look on the ceiling. The bathroom is also a must see, with a kind of red light, boudoir feel.

I got the Dirty Volcano to start off with, and enjoyed Rene's finesse while mixing the drink as much as drinking it when he was done. I particularly loved the 7 or 8 (I lost count) types of chocolate that he shaved over top of it. It was so rich it really could have been enough, but my arm was easily twisted with the allure of a free second round, and tried the Killerrr. Molten chocolate in a martini glass, the flavor reminded me a little of a Kandy Kake, and I'm not complaining.
Excellent service, very prompt and organized. I would recommend this company and plan to use them in the future.

The upstairs is a great place to hang out, work, etc.  I love it.

Stumptown coffee is my favorite and they brew it strong, which I love.

HOWEVER, $2.20 for a small coffee?  Seriously?  

Coffee places that don't open before 7 piss me off.

Yikes. I stayed here with my husband and baby for four days this week and found some horrific stuff. The sides of our bed had chewing tobacco spat out on the carpet. Obviously our room wasn't cleaned thoroughly... I'm just glad my baby isn't crawling and nibbling yet. When I told the front desk about it the kid (probably younger than me and I'm 25) Didn't even apologize and just said "we will clean it up." Okay. When? Tomorrow? Now? I let him know I was glad my baby isn't crawling yet, and I got ignored and that was that. Also my in-laws were staying with us and they had a do not disturb sign on their door. That didn't stop the cleaning lady apparently! She barged right in while my father in law was in the bathroom, no knock or anything. She walked around the room for a few minutes and then left. What the heck? That plus this hotel does not include breakfast. Wasn't my favorite stay.

I stopped in tonight with my wife. We wanted a quick meal. We were promptly seated and introduced to Shaun as our waiter. A women named Mary, who we later found out is the owner, greeted us at our table and thanked us for stopping in and said if we needed anything to just ask. I had the sausage lentil soup to start. It was delicious! My wife ordered the Pollo Rosa Maria and she liked it. The sauce was very good. I had the Margherita pizza. It was fresh, thin and good!! We will be back!

I tried their spaghetti and meatball platter and it was absolutely disgusting.  Spaghetti was completely mushy with awful sauce and meatballs. Salad was pretty pathetic as well. Don't know about other food but this was not a good indication

beset chinese in town!!! everything is presented in a appealing manner with great lunch specials!!!! Everything made is fresh and the generals chicken is bomb!!!!

The only disappointment is they dont have one closer to where i live. haha

Definitely did not live up to the hype.

Seeing the one $ symbol, the 200+ reviews, and the 4 star rating, I was preparing myself for a treat. Many of the reviews mentioned some fatty lines, so I thought this must be some good stuff.

I ate at this place later in the night so I did not have to wait in any line at all...yet, there was still a pretty long wait between the time I ordered and the time I actually got my food. During that long time I had the time to think about a lot of things, including how good that food must taste after all the hype and the time it took to prepare it.

and boy was I let down. To be fair, I did not order one of the more fancy items on the surprisingly short menu- I ordered some tacos. When the tacos were finally prepared, however, I just saw some meat on some tortillas...I thought, ok, maybe the meat/tortillas tastes amazing. After the 5 mins it took me to finish the 2 orders of tacos I ordered, I thought, wow...how did this place get such good reviews? Everything about the place/food was mediocre at best.

Normally, I would be a fan of simplicity but the food has got to be top notch at the simplest level. I can't say that the beef and tortillas tasted anything different than what I have had at any other restaurant. That said, I've also gotten a lot more at other mexican restaurants. They at least give me tacos with lettuce and pico de gallo and maybe even guac. 

If there are indeed the long lines during the day, you will not find me there.

This is one nice bowling alley.

I honestly would never have known that this place existed if it wasn't for my work scheduling events here.  Most recently we rented out the entire Alley for 4 hours on a Saturday night.  Everyone had so much fun!

The bowling area is huge.  There is also a full restaurant/bar area that makes you feel like you are not even in a bowling alley.  There are also a ton of other games such as pool, darts, and a full arcade.

The food was much better than typical bowling alley fare and the staff was very friendly.  I likely won't be a regular here due to it's inconvenient distance from my home, but I can certainly appreciate what a clean and nice bowling alley this is!

We ordered food to go Had I known what they did I would of sent it back ... Had a simple bean and cheese burrito with lettuce and guacamole inside OK so how can they mess that up ? Well they covered it with sauce and heated it YUCK    I do not like cooked lettuce and avocado ..... the whole thing tasted like the enchilada sauce that was on it  with mush inside. I think I will pass on this place.

This was definitely worth the 45 minute wait on a hot Saturday afternoon.  The burger was flavorful and the best I've had so far in Nashville.  The bun is unique and gives it a fresh take.  Highly recommend.
The Shaken Pho is great. Brings out the flavor of the meat. They have revamped Vietnamese cuisine. Highly recommended.

$22 for nachos. .. Really??? $2 extra for jalapeños 

Service wasn't great either in the bar area

Excellent gassworking demonstration!

The Morean Art Center is a small museum which wasn't especially interesting except for the classes it offers -- I wish we lived nearby to take advantage of them.  The thing that makes me give it a top rating was the hour-long glassworking demo they did.  I've seen glassworking (including at Corning and Murano) many times, but this was the best demo by far. It was done by two people, with the assistant doing the narration -- understandable because the woman doing the actual job was *very* busy. They did a pretty significant piece and explained very clearly each step, including what they were doing and why. (It was semi outdoors, so it was comfortable in March, but it might be challenging in the summer.)

Be warned! You may end up spending hours browsing the shelves of this international store.

I come here every time I'm in the Loop area, even when I don't need anything, just because it's so fun to look around the store's surprisingly big and diverse selection. They have everything from Asian food to European food and also the normal US food brands that I'm used to seeing in the chain supermarkets here. Their meats are significantly cheaper than the meats in the grocery stores around here and are good quality too. 

The best part of this place: It is SUPER clean and well organized. It is also well staffed.

There is a sushi bar (restaurant), but I have not tried it yet as I only use this place for the store aspect of it. 

I would highly recommend stopping by this place if you are in the area. It may become your "go-to" grocery shopping destination.

I've been coming here faithfully for 5 years now but this is my first review. I've had countless problems here but still wanted to support a black owned business. 

Let me start by saying the food is amazing. Unfortunately the customer service is beyond reprehensible. They don't admit when they're wrong, they don't apologize and nobody has a sense of urgency. Yesterday while out driving I called to place my order but was immediately put on hold. During this time I arrived at the store, stood in line, ordered my food, waited for it to be cooked and was still on hold!

Today I go back for someone on hospice because all they wanted was a fish sandwich. I crossed over the bridge from PA to get here, waited 25 minutes, paid, checked the food and there was just fish, not a sandwich. I told them and they proceed to tell me they had no bread. Why wasn't I told that when I ordered a fish sandwich?!  I know Shirley the owner personally and not once did she step out in the dining area to apologize. I love their food but I will not keep supporting someone who just doesn't care about their customers.
EXCELLENT service great steaks, good sides and great desert at a price that isn't out of this world.

Wonderful remodel excellent staff, delicious food the beers are constantly rotated to be with season. The owners of the restaurant are constantly walking around to make sure everyone is happy. I would recommend a scotch egg and the chicken curry.
I visited this place today for the first time and with a friend for a meeting. The service and the food was great! I will certainly visit this place again!
Legit the slowest drive through I've ever been in. 23 minutes and counting so far. This place normally isn't this bad but this is unacceptable.
Loved the atmosphere.. it was clean and the food was really good !!  We will be sure to stop back when we go on vacation again..

Came for hubbys birthday celebration.  Had received a gift card and this was perfect chance to put it to use.  On Tuesdays, they offer $18 steak special with choice of soup or salad and potato.   Steak was cooked to perfection. Wednesday's is Wine Wednesdays with half price bottles and glasses.  Thursday's offers $5 martinis.  Ordered lemon cake for dessert which was slightly reminiscent of Miss Hullings split lemon.  1818 is a "10!"

Called due to a broken A/C in the hottest day of the year. We had a guy come out who was very nice - but only after three hours did he tell us he didn't have the part to finish the job and to please pay the bill for the not fixed AC (company policy). We have now heard that the part will not be in for three days and of course cannot contact anyone else bc we had to pay a hefty bill for a partially completed job. We have a very small infant who is suffering and are at a complete loss... unhappy doesn't begin to describe how I feel about this situation. forgot to include that we had one of their service guys out in the Spring who told us we didn't need a filter and didn't even look at outside unit only to be told by the next guy that this likely wouldn't have happened if he just looked at the unit? Umm. Awesome.

O'Brien's Tampa just catered our wedding this past Friday night. I got sooooo many compliments on their food! They went above and beyond to make sure our day was perfect! We had 150 people so there's no job too big for them! Thank you again O'Brien's!!!!

We frequent this location and it's hit or miss. Today was a miss. Food delivered lukewarm and lacking taste. First time I've ever had to add salt to Mexican food! Server never came back to check on us. The Lenox Village location seems to have more flavor to their food for some reason. Pricing is fair. Lunch specials and they also take competitors coupons.

I was expecting traditional flavor, way different. Is was a good different but at the same time not a good thing. Quesadilla with pastor sounded good until it came out with pineapple. I had one of each taco to try, al pastor had alot of cinnamon in it, almost sweet. My high light was the rajas taco and it was small.

We did a large party tour and tasting at Big Machine on Saturday and had the best time!  Our tour guide was so fun and engaging which made the couple of hours even better!  After the short tour and Q&A, you get 4 tasters of their products!  Try the frozen drinks!

PLEASE BEWARE!! The dentist there is very nice and excellent. However the staff is awful. My daughter who is 13 had an emergency and I needed to reschedule her appointment. I understand their policy of cancellation is 85 dollars, however, the office manager Kathy is rude about it. I ended up paying the fee and rescheduling. Today when I was in the waiting area another patient was at the front and Kathy was arguing with the patient. I witnessed her being degrading and condescending. I felt so bad for the patient and decided at that point I was no longer going to go back there since I  had experienced that side of Kathy already. My daughter and I are going to be switching dentist. It's unfortunate that the reason I am leaving has to do with the staff and not the dentist.

Jose just took care of our enormous drooping mesquite tree and removed a huge tree stump. He gave us the best quote by far, came quickly, spent tons of time and energy getting everything right (even when it took much longer than expected, finishing long after dark), and was friendly and professional throughout. We HIGHLY recommend him and his services, couldn't be happier and will call him again any time we need landscaping help.

This is one of THE BEST BBQ places in Nashville!!  I definitely recommend it to everyone who comes into town. It's a bit off the beaten path and in a small little building, but that's the best kind, isn't it?!  Everyone I've taken here has had a great experience and food. You can't go wrong with any of their foods either, as I've tasted everything and it's all been amazing!  You should also try their southwest ranch dressing on your salad (or BBQ actually). 

My only pet peeve is when you come in and wait to be seated, as sometimes they won't seat you if you are with a small party and they only have large tables available.  So you really want us to stand here waiting while there are open tables??? Yeahhhh I've almost walked out because of that.

Tony and Ruth's Steaks located at 837 N 8th St in Camden, NJ 08102.  

Deli/Cafe

Pros: Food was hot, portion size was good, food items were very cheap.

Cons: No tables to sit down and eat at only small bar counter, menu board is hard to read, and neighborhood where restaurant is located does not feel safe.  

I went at noon on 3/9/15. I was planning on eating in until I saw the inside of the restaurant and people coming in and around the restaurant.

I went for lunch expecting to eat in but ended up doing a takeout.  When I walked in the lady behind the counter greeted me and took my order but I could tell she was wondering what I was doing in North Camden.  The food took around 10 minutes to prepare. I ordered a Cheesesteak, which was about 12-inches long, the bread was fresh and the steak was good. For around $5 you probably wouldn't find a better Cheesesteak around.

The value for the food was unbeatable. This is really a Camden locals only place in my opinion.  I would not recommend venturing here and especially not at night.  Overall, the food is great but safety is big concern and would NOT have me returning.

I've used Brock several times and am so pleased with his professionalism. He is knowledgeable, helpful, timely, all the things you want/need in an Inspector. 

Looking forward to using him again!

This Wal mart was really decent for about the first month it was open.  Now, it has fallen into the "change the oil in your car" parking lot that seems to come from inexpensive prices and discounts.  Not to be snobby, but the clientele that now seems to make up a majority, does not seem to put an emphasis on civility. 

Also, when I was in there recently, I saw no fewer than 3 dogs, 2 of which were in the produce and meat aisle.  What up with that?  These are not service animals and when I brough the issue to the attention of a manager, he just shook his head and said there was nothing he could do.

People, I am a dog person.  That said, when I go to the market, the dog stays at home.  If you want to change the ADA and health laws be honest about it, don't lie about the dog being a service animal.

This is was a lovely place to visit! There is a creamery here, lots of animals (cows, sheep, pigs, chicken) and a pumpkin patch in the Fall. The ice cream was AMAZING. The flavors are cheekily named after the cows on the farm and flavors range from classic to unique (ex: cookies and cream, orange pineapple, lavender cream, etc). 

I would highly recommend a visit here for amazing ice cream and a nice stroll around the farm!

I had the unfortunate misfortune of getting hit by one of their insured companies. I was hit by a Ross Dress For Less corporate manager. I got the very unpleasant Carolyn Jackson as an adjuster and the lack of professionalism that I received from her was appalling.  She advised me last week that she would have some one contact me to look at the damage, but I received no call. When I called the rude Carolyn back I was advised that she forgot and would send them out ASAP when I asked how long that would be she retorted "as soon as possible, if you have a problem go through your own carrier" and proceeded to hang up on me. I called her supervisor Chris Friskey who didn't seem bothered and said he's known her for years and she doesn't speak like that, then stated that they don't record the phone calls. I will be contacting both Ross's corporate and theirs. Absolute appalling...

Fantastic service and by far the most knowledgeable in Santa Barbara. I felt welcome and was greeted warmly by the employees and owners the first time I walked through the door. 
Marks professional attitude was much appreciated as we solved my ponds problem quickly and got it up and running within 48 hours. His wife was super sweet and helpful as well. Love the variety of products they have as well as the paradisiac sample ponds. Can't wait to build my next water feature with SB Koi leading the way. 

Extremely satisfied customer

Our company recommended hotels to stay at durning a business trip. It was fine the first week untill we all noticed big bites so one of the guys checked to find his mattress infested with bed bugs. One had used condoms under the bed. Mine had some bed bugs but not as bad as the first guy. The dandruff and hair was nasty. They are understaffed and even say you have to ask for the cleaning ladies to come and sometimes they do not come. Oh and they refused to put bud bugs on my receipt because I booked through a third party so they just put bugs in room not bed bugs or the fact that I'm bit up by them. We also had some guy shooting up on the stairs.

Worst dry cleaners ever. After redoing this piece 12 times since February, this is what I picked up today. The owner never answered Facebook messages or phone calls. I could never find a manager in the store. The employees called various times and I was able to speak with someone and was told that they would take care of it...and this is what I got. If you care about your clothes and how you look in them...never use this place.

Super delicious pizza (faves are Californian, Paul's BBQ, and the namesake Wild Garlic)...they will also do half n half which is nice.....the crust has a little bit of sweetness to it and this makes it different from other pizzas. Service is friendly and the servers are helpful. Parking can be problematic during busy times so I just go before or after the lunch hour. Oh yes, and yummy beer selection too.
Ale Emporium has long time been a favorite of mine. The assortment of drinks is great and I never make the trip without getting their pizza, which may be my favorite in Indy.

I rarely hand out 5 stars. This place deserves it. Black Market is a cozy, inviting place. I absolutely love the warm wood bar and tables. 
     The Drink menu is outstanding and they have a great selection of beer. 
     If I could eat lunch here everyday I would. The salads are over the top fantastic. Their homemade peanut butter is off the charts! Dinner is equally amazing. The chef is brilliant. Garlic greens, hummus, and olives? How could that work? I don't know but it was over the top wonderful! 
     My service at lunch is friendly, timely, and everything you would expect. Dinner service seems a bit slower, but it's worth it. Black Market is a definite must!
Their popcorn chicken and vegan ice cream is sooo good! Yum. I can't stop coming back!!

Go. See. Dana. We came here to get my bridesmaid's dresses and Dana took such great care of us and was the absolute best. She even recognized my cousin from my sister's bridesmaid dress appointment from last year. You can always expect a hug and a huge smile when you see her! She made things so easy for us and helped pick out different styles of dresses that she thought my girls would like. I had the best time with my bridesmaids picking out their dresses and I can say without a doubt it's partly because of her. She made things so fun but also got the job done. I will definitely come back here for any formal dress I need just to see Dana.

Okay, so this is PDQ but with burgers and pizza.  I immediately realized they were similar when I walked in because they had the same design, same fast and fresh concept, a hand-washing station and modern, clean decor. The prices were similar too. Basically every option was about $8-$10. It's also appealing to children. The place was crawling with children and families. I ordered a cheeseburger meal and was pleased to find the meat was a good portion and the bun was very soft and tasty. We were served quickly and the service was friendly and efficient. I asked the order-taker if the restaurant was related to PDQ and she confirmed that yes, they have the same owners. I love any place that has a Coke Freestyle and this place has two. Parking was easy and on this particular Saturday they were doing a children's fundraiser with a car wash which gave the place a whole happy, community feel. I recommend ordering a kid's meal because it's basically the same thing as an adult meal for $2 less.
The prices were reasonable and the food was wonderful. The sushi was Uber fresh. The place is brand new and the staff is super friendly. If you're hungry for sushi it's definitely a great choice.

Parc is normally one of my go to brunch spots but I was left extremely disappointed on Saturday. My friends and I had a reservation, still had to wait 15minutes. I ordered the eggs Benedict, they gave me lox instead of ham(didn't ask for a substitute)& the eggs were not poached enough (whites were runny as well as the yolk. My waiter came back to check on us but it was well after 10 minutes. They replaced my meal with ham and SLIGHTLY more poached eggs. I will be more hesitant about returning due to this experience.

The food is fresh, enticing and delicious!! I ordered McWalden's breakfast sandwich with substitute of ham and frosted cinnamon roll. OMG super amazing. 
The english muffin tasted home-made (but learned it wasn't) and the ham was not salty and perfectly smoked. The cinnamon roll was so fresh with perfect amounts of cinnamon throughout and frosting was perfectly sweet with more of cream cheese flavor than sugar. Excellent balance. I'm hooked, thank you Mandy!!!
Who knew Bristol would host a great Neapolitan pizza joint w/ tattooed hostesses, awesome waitresses and a beer & cocktail list that rivals anything in Philly.

One of my favorite gastropubs around.   Fantastic menu, and when bringing guests it is rare to hear they had something ordered that they didn't like.  Great beer selection. (although, I'd prefer more summer seasonals). Their buffalo wings are one of my favorites anywhere, make sure you get them with "Sweet Heat" sauce.  Fries and Fry Piles are also A+ material.  Finally, I find it extremely difficult leaving here without ordering the Bourbon Bread Pudding for dessert.  This is the most amazing and decadent dessert I've had anywhere.  Imagine some of the best French toast you've ever had combined with flavors of a cinnamon bun, arriving hot and gooey, covered in house blend caramel with with scoops of ice cream on top.  Even if everything else was terrible and the bread pudding was the same, Two Stones would get five stars for the bread pudding alone.

So disappointing, I love mamas pizza but just experienced terrible service. They charged us for the pizza and said someone accidentally took it home. They said the person was bringing it back and should be back here in a few mins with it. I was angry... I told them that's a health code violation and you need to make us a new pizza! Not happy with this!!!

We decided to check this place out because it's close to our house and serves "all you can eat" sushi.  Our normal AYCE sushi place is Sushi Ai on Dorsett, and that we didn't want to go that far on an icy night.   Goodness, were we disappointed!   First of all, the tiered pricing system for AYCE is difficult to follow.  Yes, you can get AYCE for around $22, but the selections are so limited, I can't imagine anyone who loved sushi enough to order unlimited pieces would ever settle for tier 1.  Tier 2 is around $28, and has a decent selection of rolls, but hardly any nigiri pieces.  To get the REAL nigiri (tuna, salmon, yellowtail etc) you have to pony up $35 for the third tier.

We settled on tier 2 and figured we'd stick with rolls. We each proceded to order several different types of rolls, when the server informed us about their draconian rule of limiting AYCE orders to 2 rolls per order.  He said we were free to order as much as we wanted, but only TWO ROLLS at a time. So that's what we did -- and suddenly it made sense why they offered an AYCE deal.  You see, the time between deliveries averaged around 20 minutes.  So we'd order two rolls each, wait for delivery, eat, order two more, then wait - and after about two hours, we'd only had about three rounds.  I did a quick calculation, and realized that if we'd placed the exact same order a la carte, we would have saved money.

The sushi itself was pretty decent, and to their credit, they did have some very interesting roll combinations.  But they are not good enough to be as expensive as they are - and they're too expensive to hold their clientele to such strict rules.
We will go back to our standby out west and pay less than $20 for a REAL all-you-can-eat experience at Sushi Ai.

We ordered the tasting menu that came with wine samples. The patio on the second floor is so lovely.  The service is excellent and the courses were paced well. Each course kept coming shortly after we finished each course which says a lot about the kitchen staff and the servers. The wine pairings for each course were perfectly matched. The service was excellent and it was a fun experience to get to try an assortment of dishes - all of which were exquisite.
Is this place ever open???? I tried a few times this summer and they have always been closed.
By far the best pizza in NJ!!! Tastes amazing and the staff is super friendly and just awesome!!!!! Great price too!!!

It's rare that we have a perfect dinner out from start to finish. Our first experience here tonight was one of those nights! Even the salad and bread  were delicious to start. The steak my husband had was phenomenal and he claims it's one of the best he's ever had! And the dessert and drinks were all amazing. Beautiful ambiance and fantastic service as well. We're very excited to come back here!

We love this Restaurant, 
HOWEVER... This ONE specific experience...

Last night the Restaurant was 100% BOOKED, 100%! Every major party made reservations probably weeks in advance.

Their staffing was so critically LOW, so unprofessionally unreasonable.

Our waiter was angry and absent for much of the meal. The Bus People tried their best but to have just ONE server for maybe 75 people is just ABSURD! The waiter was yelling at the bus people? He also made unprofessional comments to his other tables throughout the evening. 

The owner, Sal who is a true professional Restaurantor absolutely dropped the ball and just didn't seem to give a rats Arse. When the owner came by the table and asked how was everything, he kept walking as if the insincerity was obvious.

Just terribly disappointed.

We will still be back as we adore this gem, our hope is that Sal, the owner reads this and gets back in the saddle.

This place sucks. To all you folks who think this is Greek you should try Athens on 4th or the place in the food court at Park Place Mall. The place smelled like old dirty gease. The help was gossiping in the front, go to the back and talk shit, nobody wants to hear that shit over lunch, WTF? Then they turned the TV up? The food had no flavor, my greek salad had italian dressing on it with black olives. I will never even think of going back. If you have a young palate you might enjoy it but this was make shift Greek if I have ever seen it. Did they even have hummus or tzatziki?

Great job, quick turnaround, and reasonable prices.  What more could you ask for!  

The people working the desks are nice too.
One word...Yummy!  Great service and beef dog was tasty. Was a long line for orders but they kept things rolling quickly and efficiently.  Wouldn't hesitate to eat here again.

LOVE this place. The wide selections of sauces and beers are amazing. I grew up in the south and would definitely mistake this for something straight out of Memphis. The mac n cheese is my favorite. Or wait....maybe the fries with brisket and cheese....

Freddie was our waiter and he was really good and cool! I liked him and how helpful and welcoming he was towards me and my family. Now on to the food... my gosh it was awesome. I had the corned beef eggs Benedict and the only thing I would have changed is to add more cream. But other than that and the paper straws it was phenomenal! I would totally go back here!!

I'm conflicted about this review. I want it to be good. But, there are some hindrances.

First, the lovely purple haired woman. You made my day by commenting on my facial hair. It almost made the whole trip to have that exchange with you. 

Second, this is where the rating came down. The overall cleanliness of the establishment was low. Here is what I noticed, when viewing the cooking area you can see hand prints on the range over head. Not one or two, lots. On the fryers you see a lot of old grease around it. Then this is what killed me. The floor was slippery of the establishment. Yes, it was greased up in my opinion. I just could not comprehend why the floor would be slippery. It was not wet. 

Third, the burger I ordered was cooked as I asked- medium rare. It clearly tasted of beef and not overwhelmed with spices. The black and white shake was good too. But, the burger was super greasy, see the comment on the floor above. Maybe, it was the burger I ordered without looking enough at the description. I ordered a truffle burger. Then I looked and saw it was truffle scented mushrooms and truffle cheese. I could taste the truffles so that was good. All else on the burger was fresh. 

This gets marked down for the concern I have on cleanliness of the establishment. 
The burger was slightly above average but not the best I have had in the area.

This CSA makes my life so much easier. I love the variety of offerings and knowing that I am supporting a not only a more sustainable option for sourcing my food, but local farmers and communities! I get the Small Farmer's Subscription for fruits and vegetables and an egg subscription, and I love how affordable it is, as well as that it introduces me to new things! The website is also great and makes it so easy to customize my order before drop-off. Customer service is excellent. Any time I've had a problem or confusion, they took care of it immediately. I felt listened to and respected. They are down to earth and they care! Love everything about this organization.
What a laid back places to enjoy the good foods they provide. The service is quick and laid back and I love it! The staff is awesome

Amber D. You deserve a 5star.
Thank you for reminding us that customer service is alive and well in Boise Idaho. 
For 3 hours you did not change your demeanor or smile. Your consistency and smile left us appreciative of who you are and the work ethic you provide this establishment. 
You are appreciated, unforgettable, and I am grateful to have had you as our server on my trip home. 

Thank you

This is a nice, fun location near butler, broad ripple, meridian Kessler. Large seating area inside and some seating outside. This is by far my favorite I e cream! Always delicious! Try the black raspberry chocolate chip!

Love this restaurant! What an amazing and inventive menu and intimate decor and space. Essentially modern Italian fare. They have a wonderful bar with wine, beer and craft cocktails. My friend and I had for the appetizer, the Crispy Eggplant, tomato marmalade, truffle cheese fonduta. Nice and lightly fried, not too heavy. For the meal we had the Branzino, escarole, white beans, roasted peppers, garlic lemon olive oil and Rustic Bolognese, beef short rib, braised pork, tomato, calamarata pasta, Ricotta.
