Everything was cooked perfectly! Nice and light branzino with a hearty bean side dish. The bolognese had wonderful flavor with tender short rib. They have a varied wine list as well featuring Italian wines and our sever gave great recommendations and even let us taste some of the wines to make our choice. There's a parking garage right above the restaurant but also on the back street you can sometimes find parking if you don't get there too late.

The food was average and uninspiring. On the other hand, perhaps it is not their fault as they are trying to mimic a cuising that is over 200 years old.  Regardless, we went due to the colonial theme and were ultimately very disappointed. The servers all wore period costumes, but there was no attempt to "stay in character." The most interesting thing about the meal was the aluminum water goblets.

The reason this is a one star review was due to management. There was a very large party of 20-40 people on the other side of the room. Another party of 15-20 was seated behind us. This party had requested a private room and was told that they could get one. To their dismay, management felt that a large room with 30+ people was private. When they complained, they were told there was no other option.  Obviously this didn't affect us, but clearly revealed that this establishment targeted one time diners.

To sum all of this up, City Tavern has no locals, is full of tourists, and frankly could care less about attracting regulars. This is a classic tourist trap that didn't deserve our patronage, and anyone who truly appreciates food should stay far away.

Good food and lots of it at a good price. I'm glad I followed my gut feeling on this one. Being on the road a lot I depend on others reviews and I'm glad to say that this place did not disappoint. It's not a restaurant for dates or anything, but if you're hungry and need some good grub this is an easy choice.

Our experience with Waste Pro over the past couple of years has been terrible! Their garbage pickup is sporadic at best and they've apparently all together stopped picking up our recycling. And this is even worse since they've raised their rates a while back!!! My husband leaves the recycling at the curb in hopes that they will eventually collect and has seen them just throw it into the truck with the garbage! That's even we're even lucky to have the garbage picked up. What exactly are we paying for?! Extremely unreliable!!! They're stealing money from people and are getting away with it! They deserve less than a star!
I found Affordable Weaver professional and affordable.  They made great suggestions, were on time and on budget.   i look forward to using them again soon.

Very disappointed. I'm not sure if this restaurant has not figured out how to operate in a Covid world or has just lost its luster, but our experience here tonight was terrible. I don't anticipate returning soon.

This is the way hibachi is suppose to be. Sit around a large hot surface, talk a little, order your meal, and watch it get cooked in front of you with some cool tricks along the way. They definitely keep you entertained as you watch your food get cooked. All the meals come with some miso soup to start. Than a chef comes and makes up some fried rice for everyone's meal. Than they bring out the veggies and all the meats and main proteins for the meal. After they are done cooking the chef puts it right into your plate so you can eat it. It's all very tasty and hot off the grill. If you've never had hibachi this is a great place to try it out. If you had hibachi before this will feel very familiar. All the food is very yummy. If you go with a group you might be able to try some of your neighbors food if they don't eat it all too fast. This is a great place for groups because all the seating is wrap around. It does get a little loud during cooking with the fan on, but there still a good amount of time to talk before and after the cooking. 

All in all great food, it's about $20 a plate but you get a good amount.

I had my first lesson at this place and I had the rudest person teaching me. I believe his name was Raheem, and he was absolutely terrible. Instead of actually teaching me, he was yelling at me majority of the time. I was parking for the first time and could not even concentrate and focus because of all his yelling. He was constantly saying, "Girl, what do you think you're doing?!?" 
At some points my phone went off, and he was like, "Wow you have friends?" Terribly rude and unprofessional. 
I paid $80 for a lesson, not for someone to constantly yell at me. Not to mention, he was on the phone while 'teaching' me. 
I am only giving 2 stars for this place instead of 1 because the person I scheduled an appointment with was kind enough to call me and ask how my driving lesson went afterwards and apologized for Raheem and assured that the next time I schedule an appointment I would never get him again. If you get him, I advise you to save your money and ask for someone else.

Stayed for two nights and the hotel lobby is beautiful! Love the 24/7 coffee! There is still construction going on right now and parking is difficult and VERY tight especially if you have a large truck like we do. The room was clean and updated. No microwave in the room which stinks cause we couldn't heat up our left overs or the popcorn we brought! The pool is on the 5th floor and has a view, pretty cool. The complimentary breakfast was nice but not many hot options; which is hard because we went and there was many people and TONS of people in line to make their own waffles ( which is time consuming 2-3 min to fully prepare each one) so the line seemed like forever. Only other hot options were eggs (blah) & bacon. Rest were muffins, fruit, cereal, oatmeal and such. But it was still good (&free). Didn't really come into contact with many staff as you park in the garage (4 floors) and can take an elevator from parking garage to floor.. and since pool was on 5th floor we never saw any staff. Overall good experience.
Great place for a after work bite to eat or meet up with friends.  Good drinks good food. Decent prices with good servers.
I had a leak and agile plumbing rushed right over to fix asap! Grateful to Michael & Lea for their fast , friendly , fair professional help! Highly recommend their service
Good selection of beer on tap and good was awesome .gotta try the pretzel balls and beer cheese

I couldn't believe that this is the very same place that I've walked past numerous times on mainstreet, Huntington, LI, NY, and never once thought of going inside. It wasn't until I noticed the Newsday articles hanging on the walls inside here that I saw a pic of the Huntington store that I had a brainblast! After my Yelp app and the many positive Yelp reviewers, I was guided here with my girlfriend any boy did that moment solidify my trust in Yelp. 

I've been here three times and I've always ordered the same thing, the Falafal wrap. I've had bites of others which were good-ok but I lve the Falafal. Perhaps I shouldn't trust nor bother with falafal that's not made from an exclusive middle eastern eatery but I don't care, it's good here. It's also especially filling with the fries and the many assortments of "sauces" to chose from. You choose from 1 sauce but I'm sure if you ask super nicely, you may be able to get a second ;) (I don't know what I'm saying, I'm just messing,) 

Disclaimer: When I came here trying to get the check-in Yelp deal 5.95 for a wrap and fries, I was told that the place stopped accepting that deal... but again, if you're extra nice, maybe they'll let you by ;)
Went here for lunch.  It was not very busy. Had carne asada tacos, they were very yummy. The staff was really nice.

Itzel was a wonderful server from beginning to end. She made sure everyone was taken care of. JV made sure everyone got their order and was engaging throughout the whole show.  Food was delicious and service was the best. Shout-out to Shannon for being a great manager and bartender! Will be back again!

I am not a fan of this Petco location because I always have to find someone for help in the aquatics department. I've been to this location at least four times and each time customer service is poor. I went yesterday to have a water sample tested and it took a long time for someone to assist me. I could understand if the store was busy with customers but it wasn't. Anyway, I hope customer service improves sooner than later at this location.

Pretty cool, local spot. I came with some friends on a Sat night at the recommendation of one of them living in the area. It is a little small but luckily there is a second floor for seating. This place got busy fast so it was good we had a reservation. I ordered their potato soup and friend calamari (both very good). I also had a glass of Riesling that was nice. Service was good, too. I would definitely come here again but would probably try some other local places first.

WE had a great time at Mambo's! Felicia B. was our server and she was GREAT! Very helpful and informative to us as tourists that hadn't visited in a decade.  Excellent food! EVERYTHING we had was delicious, perfectly seasoned and well presented.

Stopped by for lunch, restaurant seemed clean and orderly. They have peanuts that you can bag up and take with you or munch on while waiting for your order. The menu is fairly simplistic just order a burger and add your favorite toppings. They do not come with fries and they must be ordered separately. The burgers were pretty good all members of my party enjoyed them including myself, the fries were fresh and hot and cut from skinned potatoes. After eating I felt full but not full enough, so I decided to go for one of their shakes. The shakes are $5 and they have a decent selection. I'm going to say the shake wasn't all that and maybe skip it and head to your locate ice cream joint. The prices are a bit high but on the verge of acceptable. All and all it was a pretty good quick meal and I will be heading back if the opportunity a raises.

I am not at all certain how we ended up here but the ambiance is total diner and our waitress was a hoot! We got a bowl of French onion soup, Philly cheese steak fries, and a stuffed flounder plate. The soup is forgettable, with a really thin broth. The fish plate was something out of the 1970s - overcooked and flavorless. On the other hand, the fries were amazing!!! We could have just had that between the two of us and we would have been happy.

Tasty food but appears to be crashing slowly. We had trouble finding the entrance as the old entrance has closed. The food was really good but a bit pricey. A great experience but I think their hay day is over :-(

This location is in a strip mall across from the Brandon Mall. The parking lot is large enough to handle the volume from surrounding stores. If you plan to head to this location on the weekend, be prepared to wait or make a reservation! It is family friendly and quite loud.

The food is very good, although on the expensive  side. Small pizzas run $10-$15. Large pizzas are $20-$25. They are gourmet and the ingredients are very fresh. Appetizers are usually small and shareable among small groups.

The beer selection is great for a chain restaurant. At the Brandon location there is a rotational Funky Buddha, Founders, New Belgium, Cigar City and many many more. That's just drafts. The bottle menu is also large. Most drafts run $5-$6.

My server tonight was very attentive and knowledgable. She readily accepted a groupon that we had. Food arrived in a timely manner when considering the crowd. I was pleased with the experience and would likely return.
Yum!!!!! Had a great brunch here. The food is great and the cappuccino was excellent.

I'm definitely coming back.

I had the chicken and waffles eggs benedict ("chickie ben," as the waiter called it) with a side of poutine... wow! I would certainly get this dish again. The chicken was moist, the waffles were buttermilky, and the poached eggs were... poachy (?). I wasn't too fond of the little bits of ham (or bacon) in the poutine, but it was still tasty and didn't ruin the poutine. My bf had the creamed chipped beef and bacon, and while the flavor was tasty, there wasn't enough of anything but Texas toast and gravy. We both liked my dish better :-) They also brew La Colombe coffee, my fave.

Oh, and there's a jar w/sugar cubes on the tables. So cute! I kind of wish they were marshmallows so you can snack on them while you wait for your food. I was a bit too happy-go-lucky and put a few too many cubes in my coffee.

We arrived around 11:30 and got seated around noon. I wish they took reservations. Overall, Green Eggs, thumbs up.

Terminal A in the Philly airport. I got in from a long flight fron Europe after a week of eating Belgina food and just wanted some good ol fashioned comfort food. This place fit the bill. Their hot open turkey sandwich with garlic mash potato? Score. Yes, its served on plastic plates with plastic utensils...not foodie approved, but I understand. Some good localish beers were available on tap (Flying Fish, Yuengling) and the bartenders, with a full bar of craziness were calm,friendly and on point. 3.5 stars.

Decided to check this place out based on the Yelp reviews just to find out that this would be a very expensive mistake. Ordered the small beef fried rice (90 percent rice and 10 percent beef) and a crab roll (looked like a burnt hot pocket). 

The rice tasted burnt as if it had been cooked in the very same pan as the last few orders without being cleaned each time. The crab roll was flat like they cooked it in a panini maker. I'm pretty sure rolls aren't supposed to be flat, but I am not a Japanese food connoisseur so what do I know.

Long story short, NEVER AGAIN!

So we were on a mission to try the newly opened Shake Shack but was turned around by the large crowd waiting to get it . We had our stomachs set on burgers and shakes so my daughter suggested we go down the street to Atomic Burger! I'm so glad she did! No line inside , just a couple cars in the drive thru! We went inside. Very friendly staff! We ordered the mushroom Swiss burgers with fries and milkshakes. The burger was delicious and the fries were hot and crispy. The milkshakes were super thick and they give you a big straw to drink it! I had vanilla and my daughter had strawberry. Both were very good! The only issue I had was that the tables inside weren't clean and I didn't see anyone attend to them when I was there . I would go back to try another burger and maybe next time I'll try a specialty milkshake! They list special flavors of the day of the menu.

I've been here several times... and you will never find this place to be quiet with a small crowd, it's always bustling! The docor is beautiful and very down-to-earth and during those sunny and warm days, they will have the front open with additional outside seatings.

things i've tried so far:

STROZZAPRETI (pasta)- delicious! The potion is generous and with a hint of lemon juice in the mix, it makes the plate very appetizing and can easily down the whole thing no problem. This was completelly different than what i had imagined by reading the descriptions.  I saw the word "Pesto" and thought it would be covered in pesto sauce or something... NOPE, in a way the texture of each bite resembled that of a pesto pasta because of the bits of nuts.  But taste wise.. it's completely different! this has a greater focus on the mushrooms which i just loooove! and it really does have its own distinctive barbuzzo flavor to it.

Uovo (PIzza) - Another fabulous choice at the restaurant!  I usually never order pizza but I thought to try something new and the waiter said this is one of the most popular choices.  From the looks of it, it looks so simple and it really doesn't look like anything special... but wait till you bite into it! SoooOOoo full of flavor where certain ingredient stands out but at the same time, they also blend together in harmony.  The bacon bits and truffle oil are fabulous! and the runny egg in the middle makes each bite not too dry.  this is a must try!

Valentine's day menu - expensive and small! I was disappointed with the outcome... yes they did specifically say that they were serving the chef's tasting menu but i didn't think the portions would come out kid sized but with normal course pricing... We tried the love lettter riviloi and the pan seared sea bass, the love letter was good but not superb, after i tried the Strozzapreti, this one didn't stand out to me... 

the sea bass was delicious.  they left the fish pretty blank and surrounded with various garnishes that carried the flavor along with the freshness of the fish.  They had this orangey minced.. something pasta on top.. we couldn't figure out what it was other than we can tell there's a slight hint of garlic... but that accompanied the fish quite well.  this was uber expensive! for the small filet we got.. but the taste was awesome.  at least this one was justifiable. :P

rest assure, i will be back and more pictures will be up. :)

Good seats, good people, good cause- and amazing coffee! 

The latte is so delicious. A perfect place to catch up with friends!

We had high expectations and knowing quite a few Mexican restaurants I can tell that, even though they have very good service and a nice ambience, the food lacked taste (not talking about need to be spicier, I really mean the taste of the ingredients). We ordered quite a few plates, in a group, and shared everything. Unfortunately, if I ever visit it again, which is unlikely, very few would be part of my order. Disappointing, really.

I have to say, I was very surprised at having read some of the other reviews about this place. Obviously I am only a sample of one, but I grew up in the restaurant business, so I believe I have a pretty good eye for what works and what doesn't. 

I never got his name, but the guy who enticed me and my girlfriend to come in and try it out was absolutely hilarious and very accommodating - the waiter we ended up getting even more so... A free $10 plate of crawfish was given to us, just because. Which brings me on to the food: The boiled crawfish was seasoned to perfection and was definitely one of the highlights of the meal. Otherwise, the shrimp creole was mouth-wateringly good and the gumbo was also delicious, tasting very authentic.

I will agree with some of the other reviewers on the state of the bathroom (but I found this to be a  problem all over New Orleans...), but as far as the food and service I received went, I couldn't have asked for more. We sat outside, so I have no big comment to make on the decor, but I was happy with our seating arrangement. 

Would definitely recommend this place if you are in the area looking for a good place for lunch.

About the best cheap well made mini petit dinner for the price anywhere I have traveled. Although I was there on a Saturday night and wasn't really vibing on the super loud music and massive crowds after working a double shift I did enjoy the service and the famous $6 meal. It was well worth it. Found down a European style alley way across from the new BRU, this is a great stop for some grub. After 5 pm they start serving a petite sirloin with 2 prawns and grilled veggies, garlic bread, rosemary potatoes and for an extra 99 cents a beautiful salad to boot. I really enjoyed this meal. The sirloin was cooked exactly as I asked, the potatoes were lovely and the veggies too, the salad is the best under $1 salad I have ever had...good place to fill up before a night out even though I just went to bed after.....

While at Philly, my friends and I stopped by here for donuts. There was a short line when we arrived and it moved quickly. My friends and I each ordered different donuts to try so in the end we were able to try all of the different types of flavored powdered sugar and one "fancy" donut. The donuts which could be coated with powdered sugar were made fresh so it's nice and warm when one receives it. They were also known for their chicken, so one of my friends ordered a chicken sandwich.

"The Diner" is about as impressive as its name. As a native Nashvillian I had some serious expectations from this space; considering its cost and location.  I can appreciate that its size has an impact to the Southern Broadway area, but why do I feel the need to remind people that 'bigger isn't always better.'

Marketed as a rooftop oyster bar, I would suggest that the servers be able to at least identify which oysters they are serving.  Also surprising, was that the menu gave no information about each oyster.  Was I served a barnicle scraped from the bottom of a boat, or a Kumamoto from WA? My server certainly couldn't tell me. 

in Short,   
-Yes, The Diner is open 24/7.   
-Yes, The Diner  is big. 
-No, this is not a great oyster bar.  This in my opinion, is a joke.

So......if you are looking for a place that is always open with an unimpressive, overpriced food menu which may seem 'exotic'--- you are in luck.  

This Nashville native, however, was expecting more.

I accidentally booked my night here the night before I was actually supposed to stay through Expedia. This accident was completely my fault and it would have been understandable if I'd lost my money for my mundane mistake.

However, upon my arrival and after a 4-hour drive from San Diego with a family friend, we spoke to the manager about my reservation only to discover I booked the wrong day by accident. 

This lady was INCREDIBLY rude and outright mean. I'm 24 years old and serving my country. I live far from my family and the time I get to spend with them is limited. I do NOT need to show up at a nice hotel, which I paid a pretty penny for, to be greeted with such blatant disrespect and hostility. Afterall, I paid the hotel to do nothing. They didn't replace the shampoo and conditioner, they didn't need to change the sheets, nothing. They should be thanking me for being such a space cadet. 

I cannot, in words, describe the level of disgust I felt for the manager at this hotel. AND after reading previous reviews, she's pretty famous for being a (insert select word here).

This hotel would be 1,000,000 times better off if they'd hurry up and fire they're star leading lady. GET HER OUT OF THERE! You are ruining your business.

I'm not the easiest person to please. They did such an amazing job. They were super patient with me. They did above and beyond to make sure I was happy. I would highly recommend them for any of your window services.

Amazing! We ended up getting the regular tomato pie - super simple but still crazy good. Plus our server Rachael was really nice and seemed to know a lot about the menu - will definitely be going back!
I agree with others that the staff is almost universally rude, unhelpful, and absent. You can walk around for a long time and never be asked if you need help. I now shop elsewhere.

The staff are friendly and the cars and value are good. Giving one star because they are holding a $480 deposit on my Discover card and this is after I asked them to drop the hold upon pick up because I am paying with my Amex. I confirmed up return of the car that my rental was indeed paid for with my Amex. Yesterday I called National and the problem is still not fixed. I also called Discover card and they said sometimes holds can last for up to two. This is crazy, I rent with them enough to achieve executive level and they still can't release a hold on a rental from a credit card i didn't even use to pay for the rental car with.

This was a fantastic museum with a lot of history.  It was a lot larger than I had expected.  We spend several hours reading and looking at many different exhibits.  I loved the variety of ways they presented information about historic shows, songs, singers, writers, etc.

I give this bakery an enthusiastic thumbs up.  They have sandwiches made with the freshly made bread , coffee, soup  and various other baked goods. The staff was focused on providing immediate assistance; they asked if they could help answer questions or provide service at the front counter. I started with an espresso. The coffees are made with Tinker Street beans which are roasted here in Indianapolis. The shot came in the cutest little paper cup I've ever seen. The shot was  dark and rich. The Jambon Buerre sandwich was so satisfying. The freshly baked baguette had an amazing crust which gave way to the soft and moist interior. The sliced pieces of ham were tender, slightly salty and devoid of any fat. There was an ample smear of European butter on the slices of  bread which gave each bite a creamy mouth feel to compliment and contrast from the incredible crunchy baguette. This bakery makes world class breads! This sandwich had it all.

Nico's is strictly for tasty late night burritos for me, ridiculously beautiful creations known as "Super Fries" for friends and apparently some other things to other people.

Having come from an almost life-time of Los Betos and Viva, Nico's blew me away. Everything I've had has been delicious. The bean and cheese burritos seem to have the perfect, awe-inspiring liquidy consistency, breakfast burritos have a certain flavor that betters others, the beef is succulent and greasy, the enchiladas are just as good as anywhere else.

This review is actually just making me hungry. 24-hours made me try them and the food has made me come back over every other late night mexican food place, save Taco Shop. I give it four "mmms." While I'm at it, six and a half "om noms" too for anyone that hates people making up their own rating names.

A very cute place to have breakfast or brunch with someone. It is not a large location so groups are limited to 5. They have a fresh made to order kitchen with specials that change often. 

The food is always fresh, the baked goods are tastey and I love all the varieties of French toast and pancakes they make! 

Fresh squeezed juices along with fresh brewed coffees. 

Highly recommend this place, nice vibe, and great service. 4 stars because it takes a while to get food and it's a bit pricey for the portion sizes. Besides that, big fan.

I go here a lot due to its convenience. No matter how crowded it seems I can always get a seat quickly. The burgers are amazing as well as their specialty drinks. Staff is always friendly. Only thing keeping it from 5 stars is the cleanliness.

I was visiting the Tampa area for the weekend, we got there around 9am, and only had to wait about 15 minutes.  Not bad for a Saturday morning!

Their menu is the same as the location near me, which is a good thing, because I the omelet with avocado is awesome!  And of course, the coffee is worth at least 2-3 cups!!! It never has that bitter taste.  The OJ is fresh and delicious! 

The only drawback was the our whole order did not arrive together.  My side order of bacon arrived when I was almost done with omelet.

I was very excited to try this restaurant after the original closed.  Waited for the newly opened buzz to die down, and hopefully the front of house staff to have their kinks worked out.  Made our reservation on Open Table, upon arriving a half hour early to have a drink at the bar first, when I checked in I was told to come up when we were ready.  After having the Dirty CEO- my favorite dirty martini w/ bleu cheese stuffed olives, I approached the host stand only to be told by a different hostess that now my table was not available and it would be a half hour wait.  We ordered another drink at the bar, saw people who arrived after us being sat 15 minutes into our wait.  I decided to approach the host stand again, this time speaking with the original hostess that said she had been waiting for me and has been holding my table.  Communication breakdown at the host stand between these two girls!

Once we were sat and approached by our server, we immediately ordered apps because we were starving!  We ordered calamari and the lamb chops.  Calamari was fine, the lamb chops were excellent!  For entrees, I had the Veal Chop Saltimbocca style which was cooked perfectly.  My boyfriend and the other couple had items such as the Filet and a seafood pasta which they described as nothing special, and there was a chicken dish that was just that, just a chicken dish- definitely nothing special. 

I would like to give this another shot as I really enjoyed the ambience and some of the dishes.  But, I will give them more time to work out some more kinks!

I worked in the government center for 7 years. I admit to not eating very often under the managers of the current vendor. I preferred the previous vendor due to the availability of vegetables without meat cooked in them. One of my biggest complaints about the vegetarian options is the fact they do offer a veggie burger; however, it is cooked on the same grill with the same grease and utensil as the hamburgers and other meats. 
  Also, there are many days when I would get lettuce from the salad bar, nearly the same amount to go with lunch I packed. However, the price they charged me would vary .50 to 1.00. Quite a lot for just romaine lettuce leaves. They never could explain the fluctuation in charges, other than it seemed to me the scales weren't calibrated from line to line. 
  The atmosphere was typical cafeteria. Clean with mostly friendly staff.
  The cost is fairly high for what you get considering there are so many other options downtown. They do offer occasional and daily specials but no state employee discounts. Expect to pay at least $8-10 of you get a meal with a drink. I often saw people pay $12 or more adding dessert or a salad.

Great place, great food, good drinks, and frequented by some great bands. Seriously, this is a go to bar and grill for my weekend adventures and weeknight extras. You will not be disappointed by this tower grove gem!

Fabulous experience 
What a gem of a restaurant 
The food is excellent, fresh & very delicious!
The only complaint I have is the portion s are HUGE!
Beautiful presentation!
Had our GF grandsons with us & our server Josephine'- she was amazing, caring, kind 
Wanted to make everyone happy 
Nothing was to difficult for her!
Very kind & caring lady!
She made our evening lovely!

My favorite sushi in St Pete and I've tried a lot.  This place is simple and makes good food.  The service is fine and the ambiance is simple.  The prices are good too which is why I like it best . . . sushi is great and price is right, winning combo.  

They have a good selection of specialty rolls.  They have items for non-sushi eaters too.  You can get carry out as well.  They have a few seats at the sushi bar and then table seating.  

Enjoy!

I would have to agree with a lot of other people about this spot.  For me personally it was pretty awful.  Dinner for 2 took 2 hours. No apps or deserts were ordered.  
Service was extremely slow, rushed to order.  Food took 30 mins to come out and when it did it was crappy.  Pasta was stuck together and very starchy.  Couldn't believe what came out.  But as I looked around other peoples dinners looked good and edible.  Mine was not unfortunately.  I would not return or recommend this place to anyone.  Cramped and the service was bad.
Fabulous attitude free place w gorgeous bartenders. Place was packed when we were there and everyone was super friendly!

I had read an article about Rooster Soup months ago (I actually think I saw them on GMA, as well...), so when my co-worker suggested we check it out, I was totally game.

Nothing warms the soul more on a chilly, rainy day in Philadelphia than soup.  And Rooster Soup delivered.  

Being the foodies that we are, we tasted each other's soups and also shared sandwiches.  And everything delivered. 

First the Cauliflower Soup-- hearty and warm, the added nuts on top were a pleasant surprise when they shopped up in a bite (a sip?).  Then the Sweet Potato Coconut Curry?  Amazing.  The flavor was bright and light, but felt just like a curry - the coconut flavor was delightful. 

The sandwiches we had were pretty darn good, too.  Now, the waiter disclosed they were trying some new breads, so I'm giving them some leeway there - the bread for the chicken schnitzl sandwich was great, but not right for the chicken, it just didn't hold up to it.  I'd love to get my hands on a few pieces for an avocado toast with some over easy eggs though.  Despite the bread, which I only questioned because the waiter wanted our feedback, the sandwich was strong.  But the mushroom cheesesteak shown brightly.  The mushrooms and kale were meaty and very flavorful.  It was a great and filling sandwich. 

All in all, Phenomenal Soups (I'll be picking up quarts, I'm sure), good and great sandwiches, and warm hearts.  How can you not love a place that donates its proceeds to charity?!

First of all. It's beautiful. From the vintage-y deocorated walls, to the wrap around bar, the comfy couches and twinkling lights...atmosphere...they got it covered. It feels very, "New York" to me. 
We dined on a busy Friday night with a 9:30 reservation for my friend's birthday dinner. It was crowded, but we were still able to order a drink at the bar before our table was ready and hang out on one of the couches. We were called promptly to our table a little before 9:30. (This was the earliest reservation I could get for a Friday night callling from the Monday before..so if you want to dine on a weekend probably best to make the reservation early).
The food is delicious and so are the drinks. Food is served by small plates and perfect for sharing and trying many. We had:
Lamb meatballs- They were good. Hearty with tomato sauce. This is a personal prefrence but the sauce was a little on the sweet side for me. I like saltier, garlic-y sauces...but suffice it to say they were eaten in seoncds.
Mushroom farro salad: delicious...balanced, gone in seconds
Smoked octupus pizza- so good. mozzerella, broccolini, almond and red chili. Great choice.
Brussel sprouts- perfect. roasted just right with garlic and chestnut streusel.
Diver scallops- I am a sucker for scallps and usually order if they are on the menu. These did not disappoint. Served with fennel and pistachio mustard. Seasoned and cooked perfectly. So lovely.
Dessert- apple pie...served in a mini skillet with creamy, butter pecan ice cream. This was so very good. Buttery, apple-y goodness.
We also had delicous, well balanced cocktails and great service. 
I love this place. It's not an intimiate evening, so if you're looking for a quiet dinner with a low-key vibe, this is not your place. But if you're up for a sweet menu meant for sharing with signature cocktails and great city night life...this could be it. 
And  once again I must mention...it's beautiful

Came to Reno to visit family. Wife and I wanted to have a special dinner. Daughter told us about this hidden gem. We had never heard of before. 
Luckily for us she made a reservation for us weeks ago. 
When we arrived we were seated immediately by a very friendly young lady (I think her name was Mya). Our server came over shortly after we arrived. Blake has got to be one of the best servers we have ever had. He was friendly, engaging and very knowledgeable. We had brought our own bottle of wine, which he seemed to know a lot about. Wife ordered lobster and I got the filet. Food was amazing. I always order salad with my meal but Blake recommended the soup....it was amazing. I'm sure glad I tried it. Blake seemed to always be there when we needed him to but never overbearing. I will definitely tell all my friends when in Reno they have to come here and they have to ask for Blake.
My favorite restaurant in Clearwater service , excellent, andbianche no question drinks prices can be lower !!!!0

Came into NJ/Philly for the weekend, from good ol' Baltimore. Was planning to travel down to Philly for a drinkfest but chose to stay local to the hotel I was staying at, so we stopped at Clancy's instead. Imagine my surprise when a friday night at this place was pretty much dead. There were about 5 couples who were eating and about 5 of us at the bar. The DJ was spinning pretty decent music but there is no dance floor. The atmosphere was pretty chill, but I guess that should be expected since it is a pub. The bartender, Kyle (who is a female) rules! Super sweet and friendly staff that will def take care of you. If you're looking for a chill time this is the place to be but don't expect a heavy crowd on the weekends, its mostly for the locals.

Great view, thats it. Entire table was sticky.Took 10 mins to even have someone come to our table for drink orders. None of the servers knew where any of the tables were-we literally watched our app go to each of the 8 tables before it finally hit ours. The food was WAY over salted. Our refills took forever and when asked about a beer i ordered and never recieved to be removed from our bill, the server said "Well, its over on the bar", as if i should have gotten it myself. 
Never again.

I had managed to rush over here with just 10 minutes before closing time. Thankfully the workers were nice enough to still serve me!

I ordered the thit nhuong banh mi, a $4.50 sandwich. It consists of grilled pork and everything else that usually comes with a typical vietnamese banh mi sandwich (cucumbers, cilantro, jalapeño, pickled carrots and daikons). They filled the sandwich up pretty well with the ingredients. Truthfully, I think the price is expensive for a banh mi sandwich, especially in Philly too.

The service here was nice enough to serve me even though I came in so late, so that was a plus! Honestly, I'm really curious as to how they store their meats here because it looked as if they were planning on just leaving it there overnight to be reused without refrigeration or anything. But I could be wrong. Due to the pricey sandwiches, I'm not sure if I would want to come back though. Maybe I'll give Ba Le another try...

On a recent trip to Canada, a friend and I stopped by a few restaurants. I'm on my way back to the states, so I thought I'd write a few reviews of some of the places we'd visited. 

To be frank, the service here sucked.

  We came in around midnight after fringing, and walked up to the bar. We were looking for a table, and a waitress who was talking to some people seated at the bar (turns out they were all friends with each other) showed us to a booth. It was just two of us, and we were seated behind five noisy chicks. It's a bar so of course we didn't care much. Our waitress drops menus off at our table and actually goes to chat with the five noisy chicks behind us. They were clearly personal friends with each other, but we didn't care much. 

  She came up to us five minutes later to take our order. We started naming off a couple bulldogs and hi-balls. We had about 4-5 drinks in mind for the both of us to share. She asked us if it was all for just the two of us, to which we replied yes, and then says that we have to order each drink separately because "that's too much alcohol in front you." 
  ????
   I'm from the states, and that's not a policy anywhere. My friend is from Edmonton, and she had never heard of such a policy either.  We're at fucking bar, where there's an abundance of alcohol, with belligerent women screaming with laughter behind us, as well as a drunk old man who's dressed like he's 60 years younger than he looks, and you're worried about us? Oh wait, I forgot that the women are your friends, I'm sorry. 

  Anyway, we continue to order our drinks one by one, and she leaves us for 15 minute intervals between each drink, and every time she had come up to us, she gave us an attitude and it seemed like we were taking away from here time with her friends. At one point, the drunk old guy starts walking around and floating around at the bar, talking to the younger crowd, making them uncomfortable and whatnot. He wound up standing at the bar in front of a stool one chick was sitting in, but she had gotten up. She was standing near our booth, watching him, and contemplating with our waitress if she should kick him out. She then turned around to us and asked how everything was, and if there was anything else she could get us. 
  We were surprised to find out that she was actually the manager of the place. She was wearing a white shirt and a mini skirt and the only thing that gave her away as an employee was a walkie-talkie or something sticking out of her pocket. I mean, she was just sitting at the bar talking to the big group of friends. She was easy on the eyes, but she could at least identify herself as a manager with a name tag or something. Our waitress didn't have a name tag either, or I'd be calling her out on here, no joke. 

  All in all, it was ridiculous that it was one big gathering of "besties" and we felt unwelcome. We didn't eat any of the food cuz it looked terrible at the booth behind us.

One word...YES. This place is a must if you are visiting & hopefully your weekly stop if you live in town. Oh my gosh, it was delicious. I am honestly sad that I have to live in Texas & can't just be living in the Dalessandro's kitchen instead.
Service sucked. Food sucked. Menu not kept up to date, so missing many items. Over priced. I feel horrible rating this a 1 star,  but I would never go again.

We come in here frequently Sunday nights for drinks and trivia. Dani is the best bartender and Mike is excellent server if you decide to sit at a table. Trivia is fun and varied, drink specials are good! Comfort food is on point, also my favorite marinara!

This was one of the worst malls I have ever been too. It is not a place where you would go shopping nor should you even have it in your vocabulary. 

You will find dentists here and optometrists. It doesn't really have any worthy stores. It looks nice on the outside but that's just trickery.

I really disliked this mall.

Damn, the remodel looks good. the old outlet was run down,had shitty air conditioning and was a bitch to get around.The new jcpenny is the complete opposite. Honestly imo Franklin mills is a little too hood for a store like this. Perhaps i'm wrong and maybe it'll turn things around
Best thai food iv had in a long time. I travel for work and I'm  always looking for thi restaurants. This is one of the best. Very authentic

Totally unhelpful and knowledgeable. Self check out would've been filled with more personality. They didn't even know their beverages and didn't make any attempt to find out my needs. Will not be back went back to Publix!

As a tea enthusiast, I tried Firepot Chai yesterday and absolutely loved it. Not only do they have teas handpicked from around the world, but the atmosphere is carefully curated to create an inspiring experience.

Such amazing service and food choices.  My mom and I shared a couple different plates and there was not one bad dish, everything was equally as yummy as the next.  Whenever I want to relax in a great atmosphere I always recommend going to The Living Room.

I was there around 3pm for a late lunch with my family. The atmosphere is nice and  the location good but the food is ordinary and overpriced. The rice tasted like it had been sitting there a while.  Same thing with the raw fish. I The only thing really good was the hot green tea.  I won't go back.

Wow! What a delicious surprise today as we enjoyed an amazing lunch from Great Harvest! When healthy, fresh food tastes this good its a WIN-WIN! Can't wait to enjoy more and more of the menu! 
Ward Herbert 
GM Genesis Diamonds
Great wine and atmosphere!  If you are lucky, Frank, the owner, will share his vast knowledge on all things wine.  We tried some excellent German wine.  Cozy ambience.
Chicken was cooked to perfection but something is off with the sauces. We tried two different sauces. One was the Medium. Both tasted so gross.

I as well have had a poor experience here.  The care is pleasant enough but, like other people, my first time I waited for an hour or so with no explanation of delay.  My second time I waited over and hour and then they weren't even able to provide me services.
The staff seems under prepared and they openly discuss other patients out in the open for all to hear- HIPPA violation!  
I really want to like this place, but I just can't.  Nor can I recommend it to anyone.

I loved the food, atmosphere, and staff here. My boyfriend and mine's trip was off to a bad start when our hotel switched our room to a downgrade without notifying us. We looked up nearby restaurants and this place came up. They were listed as being open until ten but they actually close at nine. Our waiter, Andrew was absolutely gracious and encouraged us to stay and eat despite the fact that they were closing soon. It ended up being incredibly romantic since we were they only ones. Amazing!!
I come here primarily for the awesome cake slices. So fresh and such a delicious homemade taste. My other fav is the banana bread.

I have never been loyal to a nail place and this is the only place where i know most girls are very skilled specially with dipping powder. They carry all the OPI colors and many other brands. I love going to Salem, shes so talented, fast and good at her job! She leaves my nails looking super natural, clean and shaped really well. Shes also very nice and charming!!

Called Eric to setup an appointment at our home based on positive reviews on Yelp and Next Door. Reviews were spot on. Eric was on time, courteous, knowledge and clean. In about a little over an hour, the job was completed. All around great experience.
do to the condescending nature of staff , not dr. ali nairiza i am getting very frustrated with the staff at nevada advanced pain specialists !!!

was  on vacation in tampa i was asking around my hotel where to go for a fun night out and have a good no to expensive dinner. I was directed to this gastro pub. i came in around 8 pm was seated right away i was suprised at the decor it was really new and cool for a tampa place had alot of tv's and very cool tiki bar outside. the crowd was cool a mix of young and middleaged people with alot of good looking girls! i ordered the burger with beer cheese and coming from newyork i had to say one of the best burgers i had in a long time and priced very fair!  i really recommend this place nice people good atmosphere and great food with a very cool tiki bar outside to enjoy the warm nights!
Freshest seafood around. Will ship out of state to meet your seafood! I recommend Wahoos right next door where you can watch them Foley the fish you are about to enjoy! They ship to anywhere in USA.

THIS is a really cool place! A "Revived historic inn with antique-industrial decor & American tavern."
It was cold and crappy-rainy when we were up there a few days ago and found this really nice comfortable, cozy, eclectic fun place. I had a Gran Marnier, to warm my bones, the "Chipotle Shrimp Tacos". Chipotle Marinated Shrimp, Black Bean Puree, Pickled Asian Slaw, Tropical Fruit Salsa, Avocado-YUM!! Not sure why I got the shrimp tacos because, gee! I can get those anytime I want here in West Palm Beach, lol! But they sounded good and were really were. I have to say that when I have gotten them here in Florida there's not much shrimp, but these?? There were a lot of shrimp and they were really good! My boyfriend had the "Sout Side Beef Sangwitch". A Sliced Steak, Giardiniera Relish, Gruyère, Au Jus Grilled Long Roll with fries. I would go back if I do go back into that area. But there are so many great places up there that I may never make it.
The waitress was very friendly and accommodating. I just loved the town and the whole ambiance of this place.
Hopefully this makes someone's choice of where to go to easier to choose.

I decided to try out lash extensions after seeing a couple of my friends have them and loving it! My friend suggested going to her lady, which was where she got her hair done. But I googled a few places, checked some reviews, and decided to try out Couture Lash and I am very glad I did! Chelsea dos a wonderful job, she was very very knowledgable in this and was able to answer all questions I had. She took her time and made sure I was comfortable. I will most definitely be returning in a couple weeks for a fill! Couture Lash is a must!!

After checking out the Meadery next store, bought a flight here.

My selections:
Sangria: My wife said this was great and wouldn't share.
Hazy-Weizen Orange Wheat: Did not like this one.
Hazelnut Brown: Very good
PB Chocolate Stout: Very good

The brewery was very roomy with a good vibe....be sure to look up and check out the Big Ass Fan....that thing is huge!

Will be back to try out some more flavors.

The Flying Saucer is my favorite coffee shop in the city. Here are just a few reasons why:
-The coffee here is La Colombe Torrefaction - in my opinion, the best local coffee-roaster. 
-The coffee and espresso drinks are waaaay cheaper than Mugshots, of equal if not better quality, and the place doesn't turn into a zoo on the weekends. 
-There is indoor and outdoor seating, places to lock up your bike or tie up your dog leash (there's even a water bowl for the pups).
-If you hang out here even semi-regularly, you'll make new friends. Everyone there is so friendly; I certainly have the Saucer to thank for expanding my social circle considerably. 
-Did I mention that it's on a corner with THREE bus lines, so stop in and grab a cup while you're waiting on the bus!

Came here for cocktails and a quick bite to eat before a pacers game. We started with the oysters Rockefeller which were delicious and quite large. Then we split the ahi tuna as we had a late lunch that day. Both were incredible. My boyfriend had an espresso martini and I had the Manhattan. The bartender made me his own make on a Manhattan and I'm glad he did because I liked it much better than theirs with peach in it. Great service and such a lovely place. Can't wait to go back.
Amazing warm decor! Profesional staff., good customer service., good quality massages! I will definitely come back to this amazing place.

Had a great lunch. Service sitting at the counter was perfect. We had a b&w milkshake, blt on rye, and a Ruben- everything was great. Didn't even have to tell them to overcook my bacon, they made it crispy. I will be back for sure.
Love this place! Love all of the healthy, vegetarian options. Fairly priced for unique entrees. Last time I got a bowl with a drink for $10. Not too bad. The interior decor is interesting.

When it comes to American style Chinese food this place seems to be pretty good. I purchased the beef lo mien and a pork egg roll. Both items had a nice though common taste to them. A generous portion of beef in the lo mien and a nice crispy but not too greasy egg roll. I would definitely not go there to eat inside this has to be a take out place. Overall I would go back again.
Place used to be good but has gone down hill. Melted ice cream, raw chicken, unsanitary condition, etc. I posted pics so just see for yourself.

Now THIS is my kind of neighborhood bar.  It's clean.  It's friendly.  And it has a good selection of affordable wines to choose from without a crazy corkage fee!

We have been in a few times and only once was it less than a great experience.  That one time was at the very beginning of their existence so it doesn't really count.  But the next two times have been great!  The bartender remembered us, and did a great job making cocktails that didn't seem to be filled with garbage sugar.  The first time I went in, I had a Hemingway Daiquiri.  So good.  Not cloyingly sweet and well balanced.  The second time I went in, I wasn't feeling like drinking, so I had him mix me up a handful of ginger lemon and soda water.  Hit the spot and was just what I needed.

The space is beautiful and higher end.  This isn't a sports bar where you go and sit and watch the game with your hat on backwards.  It's a place where you can go and watch the game and enjoy some adult time.  It feels like the total opposite of so many bars these days.  It's classy and refined but nowhere near pretentious.

I haven't had an opportunity to try the food offerings yet, but it's on the to do list.  But for now, it's great to have a bar within walking distance that caters to adults wanting to act like adults in an adult setting.
Really good buffet.  Great fried chicken, a little of everything from the south.  I'm not much for soup but their corn/shrimp bisque was fantastic!

Oysters and beer?  Yes please.

I have been coming to the Oyster House for a few years now.  I can remember when it used to be called the Sansom Street Oyster House and the design was completely different.  That first time sold me and I have been back many times since.

Most recently, I came here on a Friday evening for the tail end of happy hour.  The place was packed but we were able to get a seat at the bar.  We had 18 of the daily oysters and a few Love Stouts from Yards.  I don't think it gets much better than this.  Simple, fresh and delicious.

I love the design and layout of the restaurant.  This is one of the places where I would take out-of-towners to show them something great or meet up with an old friend for a place to hang out, have some drinks and awesome seafood.

As far as renting a car goes this Avis location made it very easy. Staff at the desk were very friendly and accommodating. I came in late on a flight and since it was the end of the day and I was renting a car for about 18hrs the employee behind the desk gave me the option of pretty much any car on the lot with no additional charges. I asked him to give me whatever he thought would be best and I ended up walking out with the keys to a convertible Chevy Camaro SS. It was a fun car to drive for the day and really made the whole trip a little more exciting.

Like every Waffle House, this one is FREEZING too. I love a good cheap Waffle House breakfast, but the quality of the food and service here was terrible. 

The hash browns were undercooked and mushy, and the ham in my hash browns was cold. They left off the gravy on my friends hash browns and she had to ask for mayonnaise for her sandwich four times before they finally brought it out. 

I doubt I'll be in this area again, but if I am I won't be returning!

This is the best South Indian restaurant around Norristown and its neighboring counties. My favorite dish here would be egg biryani. The place is at par with other restaurants, there is not much decoration and interior design but it's pretty decent. Anyhow, food tastes the best.

Good food, bier, and atmosphere! We have been to Hofbräu in Germany and happy to have one close by to get our German cravings in, and have gone here a few times already. They have live music and great service. It is a bit pricey but you get generous portions for what you order.
Okay so I totally love this place. This is the real deal it is authentic and this food is awesome!! It's real fast food at a decent price chicken tacos are a 1.25

This is an interesting farmer's market that has been one of the mainstays of the Santa Barbara community forever. Like many farmer's markets, this is where you can get your locally grown produce, plants, and food supplies. Plus, it is a fun shopping experience.

This is a fairly large farmer's market. It is well organized with the sellers in rows. Thus, finding things and moving around is very easy. 

More than just a local market, it is also a community experience. There are musicians playing and people meeting and greeting. So, it is a fun place to come, get what you need, and meet new people.

More than simply a place for locals to buy their groceries, non-locals can come, walk around, and get a feel for the Santa Barbara experience. Located just a block from the business district on historic State Street, it is easy to find and always provides a fun, new experience.

I haven't been to the mall since the pandemic started. But we needed to hit two store in there so we made a day of it. We were walking out when I spotted this gem. I've been wanting to try it forever so in we went! 

There is no where to sit so plan on taking your ice cream to go. It's a small space but fun to see all of the toppings and the cold stones. 

We ordered three different flavors and had so much fun watching them mix it and roll up the ice cream! It is definitely a great experience for kids! 

I only tasted my flavor (Brookie) because sharing with kids is too gross. But I loved it. The ice cream is rich so you don't need much. We loved it!
Great beer options on tap, innovative food offerings and outside seating...what more could you want!

I come to this location often and the food and service is always good, not this time!!! 
My service was horrible and my food quality was not the normal hot fresh food. 
My server Diane was very rude and didn't seem to care, when asked for my order I gave it to her and she didn't write it down. Two minutes later she asked me my order again, and again I gave it to her. Five minutes after that she asked me for the third time but this time she was at the computer typing it in. I didn't make a fuss about it because I came in after the rush. My food was out pretty quick, but guess what? It was not completely right I didn't say anything I just ate it because I was starving. I asked my server if I could get crispy turkey bacon since I don't eat pork, she told me that turkey bacon don't get crispy as pork bacon(it was almost raw) One server Taychelle  saw the disgust in my face and asked if she can help, and she did! I told her I wanted crispy turkey bacon and she told me that would not be a problem. Taychelle  gave me great service in about a 5minutes frame(I wish she was my server from the Beginning). When I was given my bill while I was eating she asked if I could pay because she was getting off...  I asked her did she charge me Separately for my items she told me No, then went on the Expo line and told another server that "she asked for another egg, so she's mad because I charged her" I was beyond pissed. I spoke to the manager and he tried to take a percentage off my bill, but I refused it. I just wanted to let him know how horrible the service was. I never write reviews because I have served in the industry and know how crazy the restaurant business can get, and I have experience bad service but this was the world's worst.... 
I never NOT tip ever, but this was my first time.
This was Terrytown location in front of Oakwood mall

Cheesesteak--It was ok--very dry, minimal cheese whiz and onions. It didn't impress me much. If I could, I would've tried a different place for cheesesteak, but it was in close proximity to the Independence Park and I was only there for a day.

The service wasn't bad, but I can't guarantee that the sandwich that was given to me was not opened by a customer, then returned to the cashier, only to have no one who wanted to eat the sandwich, so then it was rewrapped and given to me. There was a 75% chance that that was what happened but it was an issue I wasn't going to argue about only because it was late and I had a 2 hour drive back to Baltimore.

Will I come back? Probably not. It wasn't tasty and I honestly thought I ordered the original with onions and cheese but got a minimal amount of both in this iconic type of sandwich. Will I recommend this place? Most likely no...

If I could give zero stars, I would.

I've never been a fan of the bar, but I never really hated it either. Lots of douchebags mostly--can't count on any intellectual conversation to come out of the Boot. 

Last night (11-15-13), however, I was assaulted by 2 large male bouncers as I was leaving the bar. I walked out, they stopped my friends because they had drinks (in plastic cups, -so I went back in with them (obviously the way I had JUST come out of), to tell my friends "it's no big deal, we can go back in so you two can finish your drinks, essentially taking up for the bouncer. The bouncer then yelled at me "You can't go in this way!" I was confused since he had just seen me and  said, "Oh, I JUST left, I have a wristband and everything?"He proceeded to scream at me, while blocking my pathway out, "THIS ISN'T A F***ING ENTRANCE!!!" and grab my arms. I asked him not to touch me and he grabbed both of my arms. I started screaming for him to let me go when the other bouncer grabbed me as well. The guys behind me pushed us all out of the bar and the bouncers finally let me go. When I left I had red marks on my arms and I was extremely shaken up.

Fact is, I am a 5'2" tall, 115 pound young woman, I wasn't causing trouble in the least and based on my size I was clearly not a threat to the two large bouncers there. They got physical and used EXCESSIVE force completely unnecessarily as I was clearly just confused by their requests and immediate hostility. I did not curse, nor did i raise my voice or even insult either of them before they physically assaulted me. 

BEWARE THIS BAR! THEY UNNECESSARILY ASSAULT PEOPLE!

Best salsa in Tucson--Made fresh table side!  If you love that feeling of a full belly and a side of guilt after finishing a rich, heavy, Mexican meal, this is your place. 

The margaritas are good. Drinks are strong.

I ordered Momma's Pancake breakfast entrée. Upon the first cut into the pancake I noticed that there was a long piece of dark hair that came out of the pancake as I lifted it up with the fork. It was very clear that this piece of hair had been cooked in the pancake batter. I immediately notified the waitress who look at the hair, apologized and took the plate of pancakes away and told me that she would have them remade for me and the manager wound bring new ones out to me. So I waited about 10 minutes while I nibbled at the rest of my food that was getting cold while I waited for my pancakes. Finally, the Manager Mike brought the plate of Pancakes out and he mumbled "sorry about that" putting the plate down and walked away. Never did he offer to get me more eggs or bacon that had obviously gotten cold as I waited for the pancakes. Nor did he offer any compensation for the meal and he seemed very unconcerned that this happen. My friend who was dining with me asked the waitress why the manager did not comp my meal or at least a portion of it. The waitress stated that she had also asked him and he declined to compensate me in any way.  I live in the neighborhood near this restaurant and I frequently visit it and tell my other neighbors and friends to visit it often. I understand that mistakes do happen but this manager showed a poor level of customer service this makes me question if I should visit this location again and the sanitary practices there.

The sad fact is I first went to Nu Yawk Pizza when it opened in the 70s in a random strip mall.  My grandmother was thrilled that there was something close to NY pizza in Reno.  

The pizza is good.  The crust is crunchy and doughy at the same time.   My pizza was wet -- perhaps I needed to let it set but I was starving.  The topping were fresh mushrooms (I kinda miss the canned 'shrooms) and red onions.  I can't complain too much as I ate 3 slices - it was breakfast/lunch.  

I had time to kill so I ordered 3 shots of espresso over ice.  They gave me 4 shots -- BONUS right?!?!  But they gave me two coffee cups each with two shots.   Then they gave me a paper cup to pour all the shots in.  Shortbreads with powdered sugar is not top of mind when I think of dessert at a NY pizza joint -- it wasn't as buttery as I hoped.  

They have outdoor seating and they tend to broadcast the NY games.

I loved it again. 
My parents were visiting and we took them to First Watch for breakfast. My second time there and I was not disappointed.   On a bad note, it took a while to get a parking spot because the lot is super tiny and shared so I don't know how they do it but it was so good last time I promised it would be worth circling a few times and it was. The service and food were  again outstanding. We had a laugh about why there is no parking because everyone knows how good it is.   It was very busy so it did take a little long to get our food, but we were not in a hurry and my dad loved the fresh juice and our waitress was nice and brought us a muffin to share while we waited. My mom thought it was very noisy But that's mom. Overall we all loved it. My waitress suggested we come a little earlier in the weekends before it gets too busy so thanks for that advice. We will definitely be back soon. Thanks. I want to try the lunch menu next time and will update when I do.

The food is very nice with good flavors. Had the gumbo and the wood fired chili garlic oysterd for a late lunch. No crowd, relaxed atmosphere and the restaurant is open and airy. I'm sure it's different at dinner but it was a great experience.
I only come here for the Monday handroll special but it's so good! Get here early for the salmon skin, they always run out.

My first impression of Bushi was during a Yelp event, the care that the staff had to make the event a success was exceptional. My interest was piqued and I had to come back within a week. 

This is the best service I've seen at a sushi restaurant in Tucson. Everything was brought out immediately and the entire staff worked together to make sure I enjoyed my meal. 

I judge a sushi restaurant by two measures, how fresh the yellowtail nigiri is and how unique the chefs special rolls are. Sadly Bushi was average on the nigiri. However the Bushi roll more than made up for it, strawberry and jalapeno are not something I would normally think of but wow it made for an amazing mix.

I absolutely plan on coming back, unfortunately I can not do it to often because it is a bit pricier then I am used to. It will be on my special occasion list though.

Good every time! 

Best app is calamari....

The steaks are excellent...

Service has been up and down, but usually up :) 

I don't expect GREAT service anywhere.. so this doesn't bother me 

The bananas foster is a must!

A*++ That's love!
Hands down my fave pizza place. The deep dish takes 50 minutes to cook but it is comparable to Chicago pizza style. Under new management now. They are trying to put the Customer first. Pleasure meeting the owner. 

If I can't get to Chicago til June, this is just as good!! 

Xoxo
Great local pizza place,very nice people,great pizza and awesome cheesesteak hoagie always going back.

EXCELLENT ice cream at a great price. Toppings were actually really good and fresh. Worker was efficient, quick, and polite. Will be back again !
I had the green tea ice cream with lots of toppings and am mouth watering thinking about it now!
Head chef gave me great service at the bar. Great food recommendations on what to eat. I will be back!
Food was okay but way over priced. Stay away from Chilangos Taco kitchen. Environment and atmosphere however 10/10

date night with the wife... and this place delivered. 

the bartender even cranked out a couple non-alcoholic, fresh and fruity concoctions for my pregnant wife. that is enough for a couple stars right there before we even eat. my caipirinha's were traditional and delicious. 

on top of that, the food was on point

these areapas are incredible and creative. sauces were well defined and the apps were delicious. the wait staff is patient and attentive. very well rounded but simple menu

i would definitely come back.

I've only had the bubble tea and donuts, based on those 2 things only it's 4 stars. I'll go back and eat the food sometime, but until then we'll mark this review as incomplete. Nice employees, tasty taro-flavored tea, delicious donut with sprinkles.

Food looked good but we never got to try it. We were told by the manager when we went in that the kitchen was backed up, and they were not currently taking orders, so it would be a little but of a wait. This happens, and I totally get it, I've waited tables and understand the kitchen backs up. We sat down and were ignored for about 30 minutes. We finally stopped a waitress and asked if they were taking orders now, and if it would be possible to get some waters and some menus. She was very friendly. However, the manager came back out and very rudely asked us "did you understand when I said our kitchen was on a hold?" And walked away. We waited for about another 15 and no one approached us again, so we left. Went to Zoe's Kitchen and it was great.
Came here for ramen and was served top ramen in a bowl. Was way too spicy to eat and disappointing.
I had the Kentucky chicken bowl Delicious! The cakes are huge and so tasty. Great atmosphere.
Wonderful!!!!!!! Very authentic Italian place. Pastries and pizzas are absolutely great!

There customer service was amazing! We ordered the bruschetta, the Cuban and 2 caramel cappuccinos to go, everything was delicious and fresh. Would definitely recommend this place, nice beer selection (and an onsite daycare is a bonus)

GREAT FOOD. do not be deterred by the sketchy dodgy location, minuscule and tight seating, and the use of disposable cutlery, hardena has AMAZING FOOD.

i've tried almost everything on the menu and can safely say that everything deserves at least a 3.5/5 stars. some of the highlights are the beef rendang, egg and tofu curry and the fish curry. the chicken satay and chendol are pretty swag too.

the only thing about the food that troubles me is that i can never decide what to order because honestly, everything is pretty darn awesome. always worth traveling to south philly for. 

two very enthusiastic thumbs ups!!
Haven't been here since our kids were in school. Pizza still rocks!!! Thin crispy and. Delish!!! Keep it up Pizza My Heart!! Oh my wife misses the figgy piggy!!!

Great food, average service and wines hit and miss.

Classy little restaurant that is perfect for couples, although the food and wine is either fantastic, or average.

Had the fried oysters with ghost pepper caviar for appetizer, which was awesome caviar on deep fried rubbish. Throw away the fryer Foret and your food will be 50% better!

Mains, we had the fish of the day which was overcooked (can't remember the fish), but bean base was delicious. Scallops were fresh and perfect. Shrimp cooked in a little too heavy oil.

Wines by the glass were hit and miss. Chardy was lacking any character, Pinot noir was okay, but both were US and should have had a nice French option available for those that like old world wines. Only four whites and reds by the glass and not a lot of distinction between them.

Atmosphere was nice, waiter wanted to be somewhere else and that was that - 3 stars, could really be 2 1/2 in hindsight...

Not a bad place. I would have given more stars, if our order hadn't been screwed up: ordered a salad, but it was missing the avocado and the dressing. Also for $11 I expected the salad to be much larger- it came in a small bowl and wasn't nearly enough for a lunch or dinner entree. Other than that,  the food tasted really good, and the atmosphere is really nice as well.

My favorite Greek place in Reno. The service is great, price is cheap, and gyros are delicious. I have ordered the normal gyro as well as the pita pizza. Both are good, but gyro is on another level. Also the fries are really good too, but only order the half size because it comes with a lot. Overall a great restaurant for a great price. Definitely the place to go for Greek food.

The service I received  at Kellerman dental clinic was the best I've ever been treated at a medical or dental appointment in my entire life!  They go out of their way to be friendly and make you feel welcome and special!  

Not that it's second fiddle, but the dental care itself was outstanding!  Dr. Kellerman is thorough and adept at his craft.  Their facility is state of the art. It's hard to explain, but due to Dr. Kellerman's  personable way and the entire atmosphere, It was the best dental experience I've ever had, and I've lived in over 15 different cities. So I've seen all kinds of clinics as I have moved frequently.  

If you are looking for a new dentist, I couldn't recommend this place enough!!
I rarely leave reviews but this place has the best service ever. The security guards, the bartenders, and the servers were all amazing and attentive. Great food, great drinks, and great experience.

Great experience!! Jose was very welcoming and friendly. I've been in the Tampa area for just over 5 years and he gave me probably the best skin fade I've gotten since I've been here. Awesome cut. I'll be a repeat customer for sure.

After a hot long day at the beach, my wife and I were hungry and we decided to walk to grab some food, we saw a flag in front of a resort saying "BRGR Kitchen & Bar" we went into the lobby and asked for directions to the restaurant. When we got there everyone was so nice and friendly, when the server brought our food, we dug right in and I must say that everything we ordered was delicious, the food was yummy in our tummies
I've been here three times And service has always been good and food has been good. I like the polo Cancun with shrimp. Shrimp are great. Cold beer.

Great little place for breakfast or evening coffee and homemade Hand Pies & Biscuits.   Very friendly owner, Elena, who is here most of the time.  Yum!   
Came back and has the egg pie Quiche, and it is very good. Toasty hot and delish.
Fantastic Aussie brunch spot! Great service, coffee, tea, baked goods. Absolutely delicious!
Very convenient location. Store was clean. Staff very helpful.  Check out was a breeze

As one of the reviewers below mentioned, Michelle is one of the few trained brow artists that has actually found her calling.  I can always count on Michelle to give me a top notch shaping, even at the last minute!

Some of the characteristics that make Michelle fantastic is that she tailors the brow shape to the bone structure of that area of your face, her technique is gentle, she makes you feel comfortable, and shares maintenance tips for in between waxings - which is key for people like me!  I highly recommend booking an appointment with MK Esthetics.  You will be so happy that you did!

This type of restaurant has some good qualities that  you'd expect from the typical classic American style restaurant. It is kept clean and we had no wait on seating . The baked pies is what you see first behind the glass case . They have so many different pies to choose from . The key lime pie & coconut cream stood out as well as the lemon custard. Ordered a cup of Joe that came fresh , with a smooth taste , it was hot and included my own small pot to refresh my coffee without a wait. I think that's really awesome and considerate. They did have several creamer options which I liked . Today I tried an ultimate skillet , that was filled with eggs, potatoes, bell peppers and three types of meat . The meal included a side of pancakes . The whole meal was very filling and shareable as well . Above average quality food with fast friendly customer service . Only regret is, I left without a whole pie next visit I will definitely be bringing one home . Bonus Wednesday free pie slice with a qualified meal purchase 10am-10pm.

Great food, relaxing atmosphere, and timely service is what you can expect with your visit to Texas de Brazil. Whether you go on a date or with the entire family, Texas de Brazil will deliver a memorable and enjoyable dining experience that is sure to please. 

The staff is a friendly and helpful, checking in on your table regularly. The meats are perfectly seasoned and cooked to your liking, and the buffet features and array of items ranging from cold cuts to sushi.

I been here several times now, and each time the experience has been consistent, which is to say great. The price may seem a bit high (45 a person for dinner) for a buffet, but it is well worth the money for entire package.
I love the staff here. They are always on time, and have great hours to accommodate different schedules.

Let me start off by saying I really, really want to like Barbacoa. So much, in fact, that I've been 3 times over the past 3 months hoping that things might turn around. I've gone early, late and during busy times and off peak... but after 3 strikes, they're out...

Pros (more like- not as bad as the cons): 
1. The meat is fine, I could make something similar with some bbq sauce and a slow cooker (or pressure cooker). Sometimes it's lukewarm other times it's hot. They basically have 1 bbq sauce that is about as standard as a bbq sauce can be. And the portions of meat are pretty reasonable. (Also, to be fair, I haven't had their chicken, so you're on your own with that one but it looks pretty good). 
2. There's a store that actually sells beer next-door (which is absurdly hard to find in this state). Lot of interesting characters hang out there too so always something to see if you sit outside. 

Cons: Sorry, there are lot of them:
1. Service - oh my it's bad. The last time I ate there, we sat outside on a quiet Sunday night and I saw our waiter maybe 4 times. We ran out of water early on (small plastic cups - which is fine) and forgot to ask for more the one time he came to see how we were doing. About 20 minutes later I was able to flag down someone (not our waiter of course because he was completely mia) and she was kind enough to bring the two of us a single cup of water. I guess it was my fault though because I only said "could I" instead of "could we" have more water...  
2. Sides - First of all, I think it may be a joke, but they say their sides are 1/2 lb. Now I'm not saying I need a half-pound of baked beans or coleslaw, but to say you're getting a 1/2 lb and then have them bring out a tiny saucer is... well it's hilarious. I asked the manager/owner about this once, he told me they weigh everything out and that sometimes the broth in the collard greens weighs it down, so he'd ask the kitchen to give me a little more... again, we're not talking .45 lbs we're talking .1 lbs. Anyway, like I said, don't expect the 1/2 lb of beans to be enough for more than 2 people because you're sure not getting that much. 
3. Food - Aside from the meat, everything there is fair to bad. We ordered sweet potatoes this time and got chewy, partially cooked, room temp chunks of sweet potato... I honestly don't know how they can serve that kind of stuff and hope for people to come back. The potato wedges (from the first trip) were also memorably room temp and undercooked. 

I love bbq and I really hope these guys can get it together a little more. If this was any good, I'd be there weekly. If you've got a hankering for bbq, I would suggest looking within to see what else you have a hankering for, because eating at this place will make you wish you had.

Ate here twice as it was just beside the Omni hotel where we stayed.

Lunch upstairs near the open air with all the windows open was great. Great service, great blood mary.

First intro to chargrilled oysters.. ammmazing.

Came back a few nights later to eat at the bar during dinner service. Great cocktails all around (the Maker's Mint Julip this time). More oysters and the seafood gumbo, which sadly was a bit bland. Great bartender though.

Really loved this place!

I must say we were pretty disappointed in JG Domestic after attending a wedding here this past Saturday. I'll start with the parking, surprisingly, no valet. I thought that was strange considering it was a wedding and the venue was on the first floor. It was quite an experience to get parking and not being familiar with the Cira Center.
