Cocktail hour was nice but lacked for sure in most areas. While the staff were mostly friendly, you could tell some people just weren't interested in working or being there. The horderves were village whiskey sliders, Nashville chicken sliders, veggie sliders, lobster rolls and Kobe beef. Now the eggplant was far superior to the variety. The village sliders I had (3) were all extremely undercooked. They were as rare as you can get before being raw. Biting into the Nashville chicken it was good. Seasoned well and just enough spice, problem was it was cold in the center. The fried eggplant was the best by far. Also cold but flavored well and a great texture. The Kobe beef were also very good but they were tough to get. The staff and the guests were crammed into a small area, it was extremely tough to get around let alone get a drink at the bar. As for the bartenders, they were good. They didn't know how to make some drinks and other drinks they didn't have the liquor.

For the dinner portion of the wedding we sat in the common area of the Cira Center. It was decorated nice and the staff was much friendlier and helpful. We sat at table 7 which was close to the door and we had a great view of the city. Salad was to start. The pickled onions were delicious. The ratios to lettuce and dressing was way off, my salad was dry.

For the entrees my wife and I both had the short rib. It was fantastic! Perfect size portion of protein. They were very skimpy with the potatoes. The asparagus was undercooked for my taste.  

The desserts I didn't take a part in. Most were your typical cream puffs, cheesecake etc. All looked okay but nothing stood out. It just seemed like there were so many missteps throughout the evening.
Lastly, the DJ. I'm not sure if he came with the restaurant but he was terrible. Everything was techno, no request. We were mid dance and all of the sudden the lights come on at 10:30, party was over and we left. No announcement or anything. Quite strange...

Wishing I could give this place negative stars...Came here earlier today to try a philly cheese steak in Philadelphia before heading to my destination. I placed my order and when I received my sandwich, I noticed it had white cheese when I had thought I ordered yellow American. Apparently there is white American cheese which I was un aware of, I had brought it to the counter and asked if they could fix it. They said they couldn't because the sand which was already made... which is weird, but I politely said okay and they added wiz on top. Took the sandwich back to my seat and began to pull the white cheese off when I noticed a HAIR!!! Not one... but THREE black curly hairs!!! DISGUSTING! My boyfriend took the sandwich back to the counter and showed the hairs to the manager who then replied " Oh... so NOW there's a hair in it!?" So rude and unprofessional. My boyfriend was obviously irritated by the comment and told him to keep the sandwich because he wouldn't remake or refund it. We sat back at the table when the manager approached us aggressively asking us what we wanted "do you want a new sandwich, your money back, or what!?" My boyfriend said he was just irritated that he implied he was lying, to which he denied... then the manager responded saying he was annoyed we were blaming the employees because they wear hats..... OKAY, I'm sorry but the hats only cover the top of their heads.. a person's hair doesn't just shed from the top.. to top that.. he continued with "first she comes saying the sandwich was made wrong, then you come with a hair complaint, I think she just didn't like the sandwich!" I had every intention of enjoying that sandwich even though it was butchered. We ordered cheese fries as well which were actually very good, but my boyfriend could tell I was frustrated and flustered by the manager and told him he just wanted a refund. To which he replied "sorry we don't do refunds, I can only remake you a sandwich." Which he just said at the beginning of his rude approach he would. He asked us about our receipt, which I had brought to an employee when I thought I got the wrong order and he threw it away. The manager continued to bicker with us and then stormed away acting like he was going to find the receipt and never returned. Do NOT waste YOUR MONEY! The manager is a complete fool with a huge lack of customer service and quality. What a great way to remember my first philly cheese steak.
Service was prompt and polite. Food wasn't bad, (I had chicken parmesan and salad), what was bad was that as I sat and ate I was informed that my flight was cancelled. :( :( :(
Average food with great views.  Nothing really stood out as great.  Clam chowder is pretty good.  French dip sandwich  was nice.   Other seafood items were average

Lovely local spot--great atmosphere and showing lots of local artists on the walls. Coffee was pretty good (by fairly high third-wave standards) but the latte wasn't poured full and foam was a bit lacking. Baked goods looked tasty!
First time eating here. Everything was excellent! Service was great! I will be returning soon!

Played out Asian theme? check.  Giant tacky budda? check.  Loud obnoxious douchebag clientele?  check.  

Why can't these Asian clone restaurants pick one type of food and do it well as opposed to trying to do everything mediocre.
This Italian food is so good and filling. I recommend the lasagne al forno and the pistachio almond cake! The antipasto as a starter is great too. I come here every time I visit Tucson!

I love Jack Nolen's! Their burgers always hit the spot and never disappoint, I've started to get two now when I go. The staff is always friendly, easy going, & will always take care of you. They've also got a nice patio outback for you to enjoy the weather while eating your meal. If you're ever looking for a great burger here's the spot!

Since it was COVID the store was not fully open, but can order either online or by just dropping by which we did. The chocolate was ok, but we enjoyed the frocho. The kids loved it and will try again once the store is fully open.

My husband and I were looking for an affordable hotel that was close to bars and music venues and wasn't $300.00 a night. We really had a great experience at this hotel. It's walkable to Music Row, Broadway, Gulch, and SoBro. The rooms and hotel were very clean and I was surprised how comfortable the tempurpedic beds were! The staff was friendly and professional- they even gave us a gift bag at check in to thank us for choosing the hotel- Nice touch! There were no frills, like a sauna, espresso bar, or fancy upgrades to furniture but we had everything we needed. We would absolutely stay here again. Less money spent on hotel rates = More fun in the city!

One of my favorite places to eat in St. louis! This under-the-radar spot has fast service, great prices on food and it is delicious! We never had to ask for anything, the waitress was attentive to our every need even before we had to ask! We got the fried cheese bites which are delicious (get them with ranch). They were hot out of the fryer and gooey. I got a side salad which was delicious and just the right amount. My main course were the fried chicken fingers and fries. Not only were they good but it was the right portion size for me. Too often restaurants give you huge portion sizes which leads to overeating. There are three fingers so this may not be enough for others but it was just right for me. I also got a delicious shake to go; they even let me combine chocolate and raspberry which was very good.

My eyes have changed and so I thought it was time to see a doctor. I took advantage of a special they were running with a free eye exam and savings on two pair of glasses. The exam was very thorough and the technician took the time to explain everything to me. The doctor who performed my exam was very patient and went though the steps twice. She told me she saw something on my eye and referred me to a specialist. She was right and thank goodness she really looked carefully. Turns out I have pretty serious condition and that needs to be corrected immediately. Thank goodness there is a procedure to correct it. The staff at this location was friendly and helpful. The doctor was set on and I thank her for being patient and looking deeper.

You have been here at 30 other campuses across the nation. It's the go to pizza / sub place that students / townies go to and all is right with the world

Solid steaks, enjoyable wraps, good pizza.  Fair prices for the area, and with tuition what it is, probably reasonable to campus students.  

Parking absolutely horrible.  Service very friendly.  CampCo you can count on to be solid. It's not gourmet.  It's not trying to be. Enjoy it for what it is.

Right next to the food court, this B&N is not quite an anchor but still takes up a good amount of mall space and shopping. I don't know that I've been to one that is attached to the mall like this, but on the inside it's the same layout and items for sale. I always enjoy the discount shelves and today picked up a Tom Clancy I've never read for the low low price of $7.98.

The frequent buyers discount program is a good deal... if you buy at least $200 of B&N merchandise in a year.

They have their coffee shop in here, too!

During my first visit to Reno I stayed at the Harrah's Hotel with my daughter. This restaurant is located inside so we decided to try it out for dinner one night. 

The atmosphere and decorations were all very nice. We were promptly escorted to our teppanyaki table and were dining with a few other people. Our chef was Chris and we thoroughly enjoyed his company. He had a great presentation of preparing our food with lots of different tricks. It was almost like its own show.

The food was cooked and seasoned perfectly. He asked us all individually how we wanted certain things cooked and afterwords even checked to make sure it was to our liking. Highly recommend this place!
Always a great place to go with your family! I love the lemon pancake omggg! I will try almost everything on their menu. Highly recommend
Very good coal fire pizza. Gelato is delicious and a small is larger than good expect! I highly recommend this place!

This is the worse place ever. They can never keep employees because of the owner. We spent $75 for a few drinks, and waited over an hour for oysters. Do we left. But ask anyone on the street, the place is a rip off.
We went there for my sister-in-law' birthday and was an excellent experience. The food choices were outstanding and our waitress Stephanie was the greatest. I will be going back there again.

Food was good and correct to order. Service was prompt and polite. The restaurant was clean. 
I had the Big John. I eat here frequently and have never had any issues.

Yummy!  I had the steak, Brussels sprouts and over easy eggs. 

Lots of flavor. Perfectly cooked eggs. 

Atmosphere is great. Crowded for lunch. 

Friendly staff

Prompt service. 

I'll be back the next time I'm in St Louis!

These guys are the best!  Super friendly and helpful.  I'm always getting flats on these lousy streets from uptown to the quarter.  They have a great little shop with some rad bikes and all the little fixin' you might need, baskets, pedals, bells.  Hey out of towers they have bike Rentals too!

We stopped in for an early dinner at about 4:45 and the place already was full. It's a large restaurant for the area, with several bar seats, 2- and 4-top tables,  and many larger 8-top tables where they'll sit multiple parties together. 

We walked through the front dining area to the back area and stopped for a short time to watch the cooks charbroiling oysters...  that's what I came to _try_ so it was nice to see them cooking. 

Started with a couple of drinks and the Boom Boom Shrimp appetizer.  Those shrimp were amazing.  They're fried, but in a very light, thin batter. Then they're tossed in their house sauce which is fantastic. 

I hate raw oysters and I don't like fried oysters. I've been told forget about that and give the charbroiled oysters a try.   Here it goes...  

Oh man!  Those are good!  All I can say is if you don't like raw out fried oysters,  give these a try.  I'm no expert,  but will certainly be trying these at several other places.

We live near-by and eat here often.  I can't remember ever having a bad meal or even a mediocre dish. 

I've tried many things on the menu and have been pleased with everything!  I especially love their soups and vegetarian dishes, but of course, the pad Thai is my favorite. 

They are also happy to make most (reasonable) substitutions and changes. Wait staff have always been helpful and efficient. 

Highly recommended.

Excellent service. Professional staff. Jeremy was excellent to work with and was not pushy at all. We didn't feel pressured and we completed the sale after working through different layout plans with Jeremy. Ask for Jeremy!

Spectacular!!!!This place has phenomenal pizza and pasta. Everything is fresh and they have interesting takes on deserts, go here if you just got a raise because its expensive. But if you want to have an extraordinary italian eating experience in America go here.

The Mutter Museum was a unique experience because of the skeleton exhibits, fetuses in jars, and various preservations of medical oddities and marvels.  The building that the collection is housed in is beautiful and classic and enhances the eeriness and fascinating aspect of the exhibits.  The museum staff was helpful and informative and the information provided about the exhibits was succinct and clear.  We left with a new appreciation for medical and surgical history as well as the history of medical research.

This was not at all what I was expecting, but it was good. I hadn't heard of it before and assumed it was going to be a fancy sit-down restaurant but it was in a re-purposed fast food restaurant off Grant near the Arby's just west of the 10. I got shrimp tacos that were delicious, and my boyfriend enjoyed his burrito. I have a hard time finding good seafood in general, and fish tacos in particular, in AZ, so when I saw that there was a place in Tucson where that was their specialty, I was thrilled. It wasn't the nicest restaurant in town but it was clean, the people were nice, the food was good and came out fast, and the service was good.

After living in Tucson for a year, I finally got the chance to check this place out.

Being vegan in Tucson is difficult- you don't have too many options for going out to dinner, and when you do, they're not great. 

My co worker had dinner here a few weeks back and absolutely loved It. She isn't vegetarian or vegan, but couldn't stop raving about this place. Me and my friend went to have dinner on a Friday night, to catch up on life. The ambiance is very relaxing, the owners come and chat with you as you're waiting for your food. Our server Jesus was fantastic. Very knowledgeable, and sweet. He was constantly checking up on us. If I had my own restaurant, I'd definitely hire him. 


The food was fantastic. The menu is very limited, but all the options sound amazing. You also have the option of doing a four course meal. Soup, salad, main course, and dessert. They were also running a trio special, appetizer, main course, and dessert. 

I had the trio which had jalapeño poppers, pumpkin cranberry pecan tamale with rice and beans, and then dessert was some kind of banana loaf (don't quite remember). 

I highly highly recommend this place, if you're vegan or not. The flavors are fantastic and vibrant, and the presentation is amazing too.

This is our favorite Chinese AND Japanese restaurant in the Western Suburbs of Philadelphia. The Sushi might be the best in the Greater Philadelphia area, and the Peking Duck is, well, I've never had better and I've been sampling Peking Duck everywhere between here and Beijing, nuff said? Mark Kuo has done his mother Margaret Kuo proud--a wonderful host and masterful restaurateur who has put together a fantastic team of Chinese chefs--Sushi and Japanese cuisine masters--and impeccable servers and  饭店经理；侍者领班. If you're a wine lover and like bringing treasures from your cellar to favorite restaurants, you'll find a dish here to bring out the best of anything from Bordeaux and Burgundy to Alsace Gewürztraminer, German Auslese or Spätlese, Oz Shiraz or California anything--I know from experience! In short or at length, if ye seek Chinese or Japanese delights in Philadelphia's Western burbs, seek no further. Set your GPS to 190 E. Lancaster Ave. Malvern PA 19355 and prepare for a memorable evening

It just doesn't get any better than this! A fantastic menu with classics as well as superb contemporary dishes. We've been there three times in the past week and each time was excellent. A++++! Great staff, great food, great environment.

Best Italian around! If you haven't checked it out you're missing out. The menu is simple so ASK the waiter or the owner to explain it more as its more than meets the eye. From the wine, to the soup, entree, espresso and finally dessert it is the best experience in South Tampa.

First of all, no staff worn a mask or took any measures for safety.  

Now onto the food, the jambalaya was the worst we've had. It was basically tomato paste with chicken, rice and sausage mixed in. We also had the gumbo as part of the Krawl Daddy's  favorites. I don't really know how to describe it. It was weird and didn't really taste like gumbo. The shrimp and grits was okay. The shrimp was seasoned well and cooked perfect. The crayfish tails as an appetizer was nothing special. We ended us just eating the shrimp and Cajun fries (which were good). They didn't have etouffee even though its on the window menu (they said it was a covid casualty). I guess they don't sell enough to make it worth making. 

The servers were attentive, maybe a bit too attentive. We had 3 separate people coming to check to make sure things are okay in a span of 5 min. But overall, the service was good. 

We went on a Friday night, so there was live music. But I'm sorry to say that the musician was not good. She butchered several songs. It sounded more like a karaoke than a professional. Then around 8:30 pm, the restaurant was already getting rowdy. Lots of drunk people not practicing social distancing. I guess it's not really the restaurant's fault. But it definitely decreased the quality of our dining experience. But they did put a group of at least 10 people , without masks, next to our table. That was when we decided to leave. 

Overall, a bad experience. Will definitely not return.
Nice, clean, and welcoming environment. DeluXe Pedicure is heavenly! Glad to have found this place very convenient.
It's the cleaner tastier smarter subway...with pizazz.

Punch Burger downtown is my absolute favorite burger spot. I always get the waffle fries and a single burger with lettuce, tomatoes, pickles, bacon, and Swiss cheese. They've never messed up my order whether ordering in store or carry out. 

I appreciate the customer service here as well. They do a great job at keeping the restaurant clean and they're always friendly.

Hattie B's makes the best cluckin' chicken ever!  This was  the second location I've eaten at and whoa Mama!!!  They are very consistent.  It tastes exactly the same at both locations, better than Grandmas on Sunday afternoon.  That's hard to beat, but seriously, Hattie B's does.

I don't normally suck every last ounce or crumb off of a chicken bone, but I go ALL in when I'm there.  I actually embarrassed my best friend.  I told her to mind her own cluckin' business and please pass me more napkins!

When I think of Reno, I think of casinos.  Sushi is not the first thing that comes to mind.  Unless it is Kokopelli's Sushi.

We stumbled upon this place by accident.  We were wandering through the Circus Circus/Silver Legacy/El Dorado Casinos absolutely famished.  I am personally not much of a buffet fan.  I prefer my food made to order.  Anyway, we both love sushi and happened upon Kokopelli's.

You can either dine a la carte or all-you-can-eat.  We decided to try the all-you-can-eat buffet.  They have a nice selection of raw and cooked sushi and also sashimi.  I've tried quite a few of the different rolls on various visits and have not been disappointed.  The sushi chefs are very friendly and I love sitting at the counter watching them create their masterpieces.  Sushi is such a work of art!

In order to get your money's worth, I'll let you in on a little tidbit.  Make sure you order the more expensive rolls first.  It is also a good idea to share the rolls with a dining companion.  That way you can try a greater variety of rolls than you may have on your own.  After all, variety is the spice of life!  ;)

Wow! There aren't enough words to describe how amazing Coleen and her crew are. I've been working long hours and my home was being neglected. I came home to the most sparkling clean home I have ever seen. Their prices are more than fair and customer service  is superb. Thank you again Coleen!

Came on a Friday afternoon and was helped immediately. My tire was fixed within an hour and the staff was friendly and helpful. 

Because i was a customer at a different location they had my info on file. My experience was great and I would recommend this location to anyone looking for s tire fix.
When you need some quick inexpensive Tex-Mex this place hits the spot. It can be hit or miss on the freshness of some of the ingredients but overall not bad.

Located on Grand (just south of Bates), the newly opened South Grand Gyro Express has become one of my favorite neighborhood eateries. 

From the outside, it looks like a typical Middle Eastern fast food restaurant (neon signs and photos of gyros/kebabs in the window). Inside, it is small and a little rough around the edges. It looks like they started to decorate and never finished the job. They do a great carry out business, but, it is also a great little dine in spot. Not because it's pretty, but because they have the other elements down.

What I like most about Gyro Express is the food and price. Everything is priced under $10. Most items are under $7.50. The Owner (former Chef at Natasha's Kebab International), is a friendly bloke. He is very passionate about his food and it shows! 

The Gyro meat (typical American lamb/beef combo) is put through an extra step after it comes off of the spit and is sauteed with onions and special sauce. It is so tender and yummy and is the best gyro meat I have had in St. Louis ($4.99). They have an unbelievable warm eggplant puree appetizer served with pita that is similar to kashke badmen-jun ($2.99). 

I attempted to nail the chef down on a name for this scrumptious dip (I could live on this stuff).  On the menu, it says "eggplant" appetizer and when asked, the chef kept calling it "Afghan eggplant dish." Low and behold, I Googled "Afghan eggplant dish" and came up with lots of hits. So, I humbly accept the name "eggplant dish" in lieu of something more exciting. 

Other excellent dishes include sambusas that are similar to samosas (2 for $4.50), and house-made ice cream with pistachios ($2.50). I have plans of returning to try other items, but I don't care much for the chicken biryani. It's a bit dry. 

Other menu items include kebabs, hummus, felafel, and the usual middle eastern fare.  The owner stated that he is planning to expand on the menu.

Tried this place for the first time after driving it past it so many times and was not at all impressed. These "biscuits" are not biscuits at all and more like scones which would be okay but they were so dry and crumbled and just not flavorful at all. I was so excited and really wanted to like it but just wasn't impressed. A bought a few to share and everyone one said the same thing. Won't be going here again. Better off getting something from the bakery at Publix.
Friendly staff. Good food locals hang there on a weekend morning. Get there before 11 for sausage gravy good price on food but it isn't for the faint of heart. Butter flows freely there

This is one of my favorite lunch places to go when it's cold or rainy out. I order the Mexican gumbo, which is something of a misnomer because it's nothing like gumbo. They take their tortilla soup and ladle it over beans and rice. I find their tortilla soup much too spicy, so the beans and rice tame it down. You can add meat or veg, but I like it with just a spoonful of salsa. It's warm, filling and good for you.

I also like their "naked" salads (no tortilla shell). The burritos are huge (almost to the point of being gross). Chips have a hint of lime and are NOT too salty and in fact, I would ask for extra salt if I could. Maybe the problem is that the salt is unevenly distributed?

Chipotle is comparable in flavors but it goes through you faster, if you get my drift. There isn't often a line at Qdoba, but if so, it moves fast. If you go frequently, ask about the Qdoba card that gives you points for your purchases that can be used for future purchases. I don't know if they are still doing it but Tuesdays used to be double points, hence the line.

A few years ago I was on the hunt for a new stylist since the gal I had been seeing for years moved away.  I found Elyse at Salon Patine and am so grateful that I did!  She has been fantastic!!  Color is a specialty of hers and even when I can't put words to what I think I want, she can read my mind and make it happen.  I also take my children to see Elyse and she is great with them as well.  We all look forward to seeing Elyse and leaving Salon Patine feeling a little more beautiful after she works her magic.  It is with my highest recommendation that I say go and see Elyse!  Your hair will thank you.

I read all of the great reviews about this place so I decided to try it. It's connected to a gas station which is a little off putting but was decent once inside. Parking was easy. The chicken was really tough and dry but the flavors were good. The cheesy Naan was pretty good but not the cheese we were expecting. Overall I wouldn't go back but glad I tried it.

Went there recently for my daughter's 12th birthday called them only 20 minutes or so in advance to let them know we had a party of 15 coming all the waitstaff got an area set up for us they were attentive polite I'm happy with the restaurant the food was good the prices weren't too bad will definitely be returning for the wait stuff alone.  Thank you

It was absolutely amazing!

The special martinis are great, especially the astronaut (the signature/popular drink). 

The food was fast and good. Between myself and friends, we had the shrimp and calimari, the burger and the cheesesteak egg roll... All of it was absolutely amazing. The staff were fun, but they didn't check up on us very often. 

Great decor, lovely location and great overall experience! I would definitely go again to try out more on the menu!
The sambar was 'vera level'. I had the sambar vada and dahi vada, both were awesome! Rava dosa was too good. This is the best South Indian restaurant in and around Philly. Yummy in my tummy!

This nail salon is over-priced and austere. The first impression gives a hip young feel but wait five minutes and the customer service is so awful it ruins it. The customer service is AWFUL. It is even intimidating to pick out a nail color because there are all these signs saying if you accidentally drop a polish that you have to pay for it not to mention it was $23 before tip just for a simple manicure (not gel)! The technician seemed to not respect the manager and they were arguing over appointments and tickets during the manicure. The manager was curt and didn't offer any beverages even though I had to wait an hour an half just for a manicure although I was quoted 45 minutes. I will definitely not be back...ever.
My team and I love the ice cream here! Very friendly people and best tasting ice cream in town. They have many flavors too pick from. We still haven't tried them all!!!

This place was right next to our hotel and we were looking for something close b/c it was already past 9 p.m. when were ready to eat.  

We were a group of 12 and wasn't sure if they would be able to seat us outside.  They were except the other tables were so close that it was hard to squeeze into your seat.  Also, the seat on the end had to watch out for the servers b/c they were walking back and forth.

We ordered the falafel and hummus as an appetizer and it was really good! For our dinner, I had ordered the grilled Cuban mojo snapper and it was awful.  There was no taste to it whatsoever!!  It was so bland and boring and I could barely eat it.  My parents ordered the Jambalaya and it was pretty good.  I would have rather got that then the fish.  I probably should have said something to our waitress, but she seemed like she was in a hurry because she told us the kitchen was closing and she barely came by to check on us.

Our condo ordered windows for our entire building from all weather in May of this year....they were to be installed at the end of May finishing in October... well here it is almost August and the windows have gone to our contractor and engineers and still have not passed the quality test.... pretty scary stuff considering this is a high rise building....

I've been going here for many years,
Always had an okay experience until tonight 
Employee Cindy did my nails and 
I have to say, she is the sweetest women I've 
ever experienced and really took the time to do my nails. I came in at 7:15 and was done around 9:05. She stayed an hour later just so I could have what I wanted, and even kept a conversation going! Generally the best nail experience I've ever had and 10/10 would recommend Cindy! If you think of coming here please request her, than you again :)
Dr MCNichols and Noel were amazing! I had no wait and needed to be seen after a car accident- they were efficient and thorough! I so appreciate his knowledge, compassion and advice !

This place is one of my favorite venues to see a concert. I think I have seen 4 here (Jimmy Eat World, Girl Talk, Demetri Martin and a rap concert) and all of them have been fantastic. It has the feel of a smaller venue while still being able to hold a lot of people. Plus if you want to drink both before and after the concert you have many choices (Halo Bar, Pin Up, Blueberry Hill etc.) so that you can continue the party long into the night. 

All in all tickets are generally not too expensive to get in here and every concert is a good time.

My sister and I came in yesterday to find a jar for her work and were proceeded to be followed by 2 ladies who work there throughout the store. Being of color and and being followed by 2 older white ladies was quite unsettling. I love their selection and love looking at things and we have bought from them before but this last time made me uncomfortable. I'll give it another shot at shopping but if it happens again I won't be going back. Great selection of antiques and local goods, crappy staff.
It was such a great experience. For the grand opening the sushi was 50% off and there was great service and the food was out so fast

What a shit show. I feel bad because restaurants are struggling, but you should never in any circumstance take more people than good service can handle. I'm sure I'll be back because the food is good but I hope they see this review. You're hosstess has no idea what she's doing. What a tragedy of a night.

We have been to Win Win Asian Kitchen a few times for lunch and dinner.  Additionally, we have order take out a few times and I want to clarify that my review today is centered around my take out experience.

The food is packaged nicely and the containers are effective enough to ensure you have no spills on your drive home.  

Both my wife and I agree on the following, Win Win is a better experience for dine in rather than take out.   Allow me to explain:

- Volume:  The amount of food you receive on the to go containers is no where near the same you receive when dining in. Traditionally there is a nice ratio of rice to entree, do not expect this on take out.  Your entree size is considerably smaller as well, now realize that you are paying the same price for take out and dine in.

-Consistency: I ordered the Mongolian Beef with the house fried rice.   I have had this dish during my dine in visits and it does not disappoint. Quite different on my take out experience, the onion to beef ratio was well let's just say that I felt I was having an onion salad with a few pieces of beef (honestly less than 8).  They also drowned the onions with sauce that had an overpowered taste of ginger.

I gave this review twi stars because the flavor is still good.  Win Win, please don't fall in the same pit that your peers have fallen to, differentiate yourself from them and maintain the quality that "initially" drew us to you.
I'm a big fan of thanksgiving style sandwiches and I have to say that theirs is hands down the best I've had. I highly recommend this place!

Worth the cruise down the river, but do NOT bother with any of their food promotions.

Look, it's not a boat from the 1800's or anything like that. I believe it was built in the 70's or something. But you're in New Orleans, and these boats are a big part of the history and you should experience it to the fullest.

As a short 2-2.5 hour cruise, even as a local, it is worth the money. You can sit, stand, walk all over most parts of the boat, enjoy the sights and listen to the narrator. It's nice. They even serve drinks. VERY OVERPRICED drinks, but.... c'mon.

Don't bother with the food. For a seriously pricey premium you can take the cruise and get a lunch or dinner. I went on the Jazz lunch one time and it was just... meh. I was expecting a live jazz band playing some dixieland while I ate some etouffee or jambalaya or other staples like that. What I got was a piano player droning out modern day boring Kenny G jazz and a buffet of bland mediocre "New Orleans syle" food. SERIOUS waste of money. There are literally a dozen restaurants where you can eat in the immediate vicinity of the vessel, so WAIT and eat there. 

But like I said, the actual cruise is nice. I tell people to at least check it out all the time. Even if you LIVE here, you should check it out every now and then. 

I think they offer a cruise down to the Zoo. I'd like to try that.
Really nice workers and great food for reasonable/ cheap prices. I would definitely be back soon!
i had the bestt time ever here with the fi! The dance floor was kinda small but the DJ was awesome and the bartenders were so friendly. def go!

Consistently great food and service. The Skinnylicious menu offers delicious options...try the lemon garlic shrimp pasta! The oreo cookie cheesecake is insane! Bring your appetite...the portions are BIG!

Ok fine. You guys get a 5 star from me too. Located in the Santa Barbara Public Market. I got the Al Pastor and the Norteno. Two tacos made me full. Homemade tortilla was really good. The meat was perfectly cooked and tender and had the perfect amount of spices. As a Texan, I'm impressed. I was however confused if I should leave my tray on the table or hand it to the staff since seating was limited.
DELICIOUS sushi! Always make sure to go with an appetite to get money's worth for the unlimited option.

This place is over priced and the selection is absolute garbage. Dated clothing with picks and pulls. I can find way better deals at Nordstrom. The man running the store is extremely rude and seems to be full of himself. The customer service is hands down one of the worst experiences I've ever had.  I'm not sure how he has stayed in business this long.

Took my 4 year old son there and he had a blast!  I wasn't 100% sold that it would be worth it, but I literally had to pull him out of there because he was having so much fun. The water area on the first floor was great and so was the construction area on the second floor. I highly recommend it for travelers who need a day out of the sun.

Service is horrible! Been sitting at this table for almost an hour and still nothing! One of the worst places I've ever been in Brandon! There is no way you should be in business  next month. Manager has been walking around socializing. No wonder you were closed down a few weeks ago.
Good wings and good pizza.   our go to place in sparks for wings. Have only tried the pizza and wings.  Staff is always super friendly every time too!!
Great service and we were sat with a large party very quickly, sushi is good but not amazing. Would revisit!
Express mani pedi today was supposed to be rushed but they seemed under staffed so it was harried. Great massage at dry booth makes everything better.
beware, dont use this company for any medical supplies. they bilk the insurance companies and medicare.   fraud
Great service and a good sandwich. I would have to go back to know whether or not this places deserves a five star. However, this place IS worth going back to.

Service was ok, when you hunt them down.  Kids mac and cheese was a cold mac soup, cheese?  Wings cold.  Ordered large got 2 cups dressing Only, xtra dressing are charged, 1 napkin per person, silverware as you ask for it...guess we are not coming back for a family meal

Started with the garlic baked clams which were very tasty. Nice flavor, good sized clams with bacon and I think a good amount of butter. Never a bad thing for flavor, but not great for your arteries!

I also got the fish and chips and the fish was fantastic!!! Super fresh, tender, perfectly fried with a great crispy batter. It was some of the best fried fish I've ever had. The fries were just ok...not very flavorful. But it's a good portion of fish, so I ate all that and just left the fries. No biggie...the fish was A+!!
Ok fare. Reliable and consistent. Better than pizzeria beddia bugs because I don't have to wait three hours for my pie.

I did not have the best experience and it was close to these reviews.

Took phone in around 10: 20 to be told it would be a few hours to replace glass on iPhone..the tech was not there yet and had other phones.
I left and got an email at 11:30 saying phone is ready..I return and the guy says the phone is not ready and he didn't send an email....after a few minutes, he concludes he may have hit the wrong button?  No apology, just it will be a while longer.

45 minutes later I return and they are wrapping it up. 

For $160 to replace glass and these reviews, I thought it would have been easier.

Also, the showroom is crazy loud with a TV running an ad blaring...

I sadly noticed I had a flat yesterday and quickly took my car over to Tire Pros to see if they could patch up my flat instead of having to replace the whole tire. Not only were they fast at getting to fixing my tire, they didn't charge for patching up the hole left by a pesky nail. The last place I went to when I had the same issue, I was charged $30 to repair the tire. That is just ridiculous so I was shocked when they told me there would be no charge. They were also very friendly and a pleasure to do business with. 

I will definitely be coming back to Tire Pros when I have future tire problems!

Ron helped me today with my snowboard. Not only did he do the service in a timely manner, he also educated me which was nice. Ron and the rest of the staff are always so friendly and go out of their way to provide their customers a personalized, great experience shopping with them. I'll go back for all my outdoor needs.

How the mighty have fallen. Fast service but the food is lacking. More locations has not improved  the food. Lackluster home fries. Middling hollandaise with only a passing relationship with butter. Over poached eggs. Bathroom tile sized plates are awkward. 

Wait staff is awesome. But the bosses have clearly cut corners in the back of the house.

I recently visited the Car Vision dealership in Philadelphia. My credit is not good due to many reasons, so I could not get approved, BUT, Sayeeda Miles was very helpful. Sayeeda even helped me get enrolled in a course to improve my credit. Sayeeda was very pleasant and easy to talk to. Thank You for providing Great Customer Service.  VERN from Delaware.

I am a local and have tried Pearl three times.  It is the last and final time that I decided to do a review.  The first experience was good...the second, not so much and the third was when I decided to do this and really wished I could give it no stars. 

My husband who works as a welder had just gotten off of a ten hour day.  We walked in and were seated fairly quickly.  We watched for ten minutes as an older female server assisted a table who had gotten there AFTER we had.  I just assumed that she was assigned their table so we patiently waited for our server.  Several staff members looked in our direction but said nothing.

After the female server took the order of the table who arrived after us, she looked in our direction and threw us a disgusted look, mostly directed at my husband, who was still in his work clothes. She paid no attention to me.  Naturally as I was wearing a pair of dress slacks and a nice professional blouse.  Her look was so insulting that I stood up and we walked out.

There is no dress code posted.  My husband was clean but his work clothes looked a bit rough.

Exactly who do they think THEY are to delay our service based off of physical appearance?  The two times before, my husband was wearing a pair of slacks and a nice button down shirt.  The same female server was there both times waiting on other tables and she had glanced our direction both times and smiled and welcomed us.  The two previous times, when we were both dressed nicely, they treated us very well. This is NOT a ritzy jacket and tie required type of environment.  It is an Oyster Bar in the middle of a casino.  The two previous times we had gone in there, we had noticed that the other patrons dressed fairly casually.  Had we thought it was going to be an issue of my husband's work attire, we would have planned accordingly.  

The worst part is that after the server's offensive glare in my husband's direction, and our subsequent departure, not a single staff member bothered to speak with us or ask if there was anything wrong.  They simply let us walk out. 

There are two factors that would cause me to never go back to a business and write a negative review.  Those factors are:  (1) bad food and/or (2) bad service.  By the server's look of disdain AND the fact that the other staff members showed a lack of consideration for us, that particular business conveyed to us that we, as patrons or potential patrons do not matter to them because we weren't the "attractive" type of customer they wanted.  In other words, they prejudged us as customers, based SOLELY off of appearance.

This is the type of restaurant that does not deserve my business.

Me, my daughter, girlfriend, and two other friends reserved a bay on December 26, 2021.  I have been many times to this Topgolf location (Mt Laurel, NJ) with good experiences. This was their first time - all beginners. We played for a couple of hours and had a great time.  We enjoyed some drinks, snacks, and comfortable seating. Friendly, attentive staff.  All good!

Stopped here for some BBQ after a local recommended it. The pulled pork had a nice flavor but I was disappointed in the 1 sauce option. 

The atmosphere on the rooftop patio was great though, so that alone gets an extra star.

Solid take-out Thai at a good price, Thai Ochid should be on your lunch list.

A really great Thai take-out place, Thai Orchid gets extra points for coordinating a really large work take-out order to perfection. It also looks like a really nice place to eat, although I was only inside for a few minutes. I ordered the vegetarian drunken noodle ($10) - fresh ingredients and a good portion size. If you want it spicy definitely request it, as I made the mistake of ordering mild and didn't taste any spice (my fault not the restaurant's). Overall, Thai Orchid will satisfy and online ordering through Yelp24 is super convenient.

I liked that they have late night food including duck wings or a little bucket of boiled peanuts for $2. It's also fun that it's tucked away. This is a cool lil divey hipster secret bar for SoTa chicanery.
Amazing food. Probably the best burger and fries I've had in Philly thus far! Such a great environment and awesome staff.
Cute little cafe with home-style breakfast food, sandwiches and some specials. Open for breakfast and lunch only. There's also an antique shop next door.

I absolutely love this place. Not only is the food phenomenal, you get a good sized portion. The bloody mary is sooo good. We got the big one and it came with half a grilled cheese sandwich, bacon, olives, peppers, lemon and of course celery

Been here twice now - solid music and great selection of beer. There is a cover charge but it's usually not too bad. I love that there's enough space in the venue that some people can be right up front and dance, and others can just step back and enjoy the music. Next time I'm in the Crescent City I will be returning!

The food is basic, if that. Seemed microwaved and not fresh at all. Portions are small for the price. Bread was good but had to keep asking for more bc they give you such a small amount. Caesar salad tasted like nothing. Idk what dressing that was but it had zero taste. The server was ok. Won't be going back.

The only place that has real authentic Chinese food with high quality ingredients that is not in China town. 
Chinese pancakes are best I ever had, although I'm not sure how authentic this item is. 
The Dan Dan noodles are the best Asian noodles I ever had anywhere. 
Everything else is so fresh and made to order just how you like it. You can pick spicy level 1 to 10 even.

Robert was our Chef and we couldn't be more pleased with the table show and his personality.
We come to Reno from northern Ca and have many places to choose from for our dining experience, Ichiban is a favorite stop and people like our Chef Robert make that experience exceptional.
Take the time to visit and you will enjoy it as well.

I wanted to love my experience at Arirang, I really did. My rating is based on the poor service received and the sauces of the dishes during my first, last, and only visit there.

I went around 3 pm or 4 pm -for a late lunch or early dinner- with a friend. We were the only ones there. We knew from the other reviews that we had to try either the bulgogi or galbi. This time, we opted for a beef bulgogi ($20.99) and the fried chicken ($23.95).

The fried chicken was not fried chicken at all. It more closely resembled chicken tenders. As a fan of KFC, I had high expectations for Arirang's KFC to rival Sa Ri One's. The sauce that came with the KFC was very good. The chicken itself was good, but it was disappointing to get only chicken tenders and have it be advertised as the regular fried chicken.

Next, the "beef bulgogi" was a catastrophe. Having clearly said, "beef bulgogi," our waitress must have misunderstood me, because of a couple of minutes before she brought the dish out, she asked whether or not I asked for pork or beef. I clarified that I wanted "beef bulgogi" and she apologized that the chef made a pork bulgogi. She asked if this was okay as it would take too long to make the beef bulgogi. We already waited a while for the food for being the only table in the restaurant so that the pork bulgogi would suffice.

When I received the "pork bulgogi" it had no resemblance to any bulgogi that was familiar to me. It was not thinly sliced, and it was not sweet and savory. Instead, we received a plate of "spicy pork," which was hard pieces of pork slathered in gochujang. I did not enjoy it whatsoever.

We did not touch the "pork bulgogi" anymore and instead finished the "KFC." We asked for the check, and I asked her to remove the "pork bulgogi" from our check since we did not eat it (except for the one piece to try) and we did not like it. The waitress became offended as if we should have liked the mistaken plate that was brought out to us.

She quickly communicated the confusion with the owner and Misook quickly came out. Both ladies told me multiple times to clearly order the beef bulgogi next time instead of ordering what I got. I repeated myself that I did explicitly order the beef bulgogi and that it may just have been a misunderstanding. I only said yes to the "pork bulgogi" because I was starving and didn't mind pork, but what I received was not only the wrong order, it was not even close to an alternative. 

Both ladies continued to argue with each other in front of us and made us feel incredibly awkward. While Misook finally settled the argument, she offered us a free item on our next visit. Although I expressed my appreciation, I do not think I will return to Arirang. Neither the food or the display of service and professionalism met the standards for what is supposedly one of the best restaurants in South Tampa.

This is a beautiful, modern, clean and extremely expensive sweet shop.

They have baked goods chocolate and macaroons.

I must have missed the boat on the macaroons trip because I have never tasted a macaroon that was good or flavorful. They taste like card board or paper with some barely flavorful cream in them? These expensive ones with gold were the same.

I also tried a cupcake which was ok but nothing great. I can pay 4 dollars for 6 cupcakes at the local grocery store and they're better.

If you're going to charge top dollar for baked goods they need to be above and beyond what you can normally buy for less.

Coming from the region we love our Gyros, and other staples from a gyro joint , since moving to Indy this has been one thing I have missed, a gyro done right , every time , this place does it! I have tried gyro places on the NW side, east side , south side and west side and nobody comes close , I have Been here twice and it hits the spot, if you want a real gyro with great service go here! It's worth the drive

I don't know what I was thinking when I brought my car for repairs to this establishment.  My daughter and husband both had a negative experience here. But with my air conditioner not working during the summer heat and our regular mechanic not being able to service my car for about 5 days, I thought this was a viable option.  Never again.

I dropped my vehicle off before store hours and was called once I was at work informing me that the mechanic who repairs AC would not be in the morning and he was unsure if he was coming in at all. I asked if my vehicle could be transported to another location since the mechanic may not be in.  He assured me that he would do everything possible to have my vehicle looked at.

I did get a call that afternoon informing me that the compressor and condenser were bad.  I was quoted a price of $1500 to repair.  I did not authorize the repairs and told him I would pick up my vehicle that evening. 

When my husband and I went to pick up the vehicle, it took 10 minutes to be waited on, then another 10 minutes to find my keys, then another 10 minutes while the clerk searched for the paperwork.  The manager was called to assist.  The manager searched, but was unable to find the paperwork.  He asked me how much the diagnostics cost.  Asking a customer how much  the job cost???? Couldn't that info be found in the computer?????

So....finally get my car into our regular mechanic (a reputable one). Condenser replaced and freon added.  Compressor is in good shape - doesn't need to be replaced.  Cost -----$500.  Yes, one third of the cost that was quoted by Pepboys.

Unless you have money to burn and time to waste, stay away!

Best groomer I've found. Quick response - they really try to work you in if they can. My dog always comes back looking and smelling great! Michele is the best. Other staff are friendly and helpful. You can tell they're good because they are so in demand!
It's alright. I thought Bouchon's had better service / wine selection.

Excellent flavor. They are large but pricey. $3 for 1 cookie and $10 for 4cookies. They change  different flavors every Monday. They keep 2 staple flavors then rotate 4 other flavors. The staples are warm chocolate chip and chilled sugar cookie. Both are good. My husband fell in love with the peanut butter cookie. It's soft and has a thin layer of peanut butter in the middle. The snicker doodle has great flavors. If you like a crunchy outside and soft inside this is your place. There open late and closed on Sundays. Yummy
Great people owner came out and help me with my saxophone they helped me a lot thanks

Since writing my rave review I have actually stopped going to Neighborhood Bikes. The first time I got a flat I took it here and it was fixed, but the next day my tire was flat again. No worries, I took it back and they fixed it without charge. But the second time I got a flat the next day it was flat again. I got it fixed on a Friday, it was flat the next morning, but I couldn't make it in that Saturday. NB's repair shop is only open Wed - Sat (which I found out Monday) so I couldn't take it in until Wed. At that point I told him that it had become flat again the next day but since it had been about four days he told me they weren't responsible for it. I pointed out how the shop wasn't open sun - tue for me to have brought it in. He didn't charge me for the labor but  I had to pay for another tube. The guy is really nice, but I don't really understand why both times i've gotten the tire fixed it was flat the next day. The same thing happened to a friend of mine. I've stopped taking my bike there, especially since it was flat again within a week of the second fix.

I came in and asked for an pedicure and a refill at 6:00pm and they close at 7:30pm. The lady took me over and started my pedicure and she told me that somebody else would do my nails because she does not do acrylic nails which was fine with me. Towards the end she told me that i can come back tomorrow and get my nails done and i said i cannot! I came and asked for both services and had you said you couldn't do both i would have went somewhere else and not to mention my polish is off and i have tried on several colors.Then she said she would repaint my old nails, i said ABSOLUTELY NOT! She then said ok she would have Eric do my nails when he was finished his customer, After Eric was done with his customer he seemed a little lackadaisical so I asked him if he was doing my nails and he said i should come back tomorrow as its almost closing time. I again said NO i came in and asked for both services and the woman who did my nails said you were doing my nails and you heard her! I asked him if he thought it was ok that a customer leave with their nails like this and again he said its almost closing time. Now I'm mad! So i kindly said I have never in my life heard of such! I'm not paying for this shitty pedicure! And I'm never coming the fuck back!... I could not believe it!

This place was far from a palace in that there was absolutely no service to be found.  A king would starve to death here and his queen would not have her thirst quenched. Stay away from the moat and go to another kingdom.

Great, standard tavern-style food. 

I recommend the Nash Vegas burger. Recommended by the waitress - great menu item.  Sweet potato bun, pimiento cheese, crispy tobacco onions (crispy onion strings), and bbq sauce. :P

Will be back!

In the midst of the coronavirus when we as a people should be uniting together and helping however we can. My Wife and I were just treated like trash by employee Andy W. At this Meijer (Meijer-8375 E. 96th St. Indianapolis) I guess that given my wife has Dreadlocks and I have plenty of Tattoos, that this Andy W. Thought he was better than us and that we didn't have the money to pay for our goods or something. My wife started ringing up our items at the self-checkout as I ran back to grab something we had forgotten. When I got back to my wife with item, she tells me that the employee (Andy W.) had just accused her of trying not to scan our eggs. No sweat, just doing his job right??? As she continues scanning our groceries, I notice other customers asking him for help, he ignores them telling them to wait, as he stands there staring at my wife and I like we are America's Most Wanted. So I walk over to him and ask if they cash payroll checks as I happen to have a $1300 check in my pocket, he ignores me point blank, side steps me and continues ogling my wife as if she's a criminal. So I turn around and return to my wife and chuckle and tell her he thinks we are stealing. To which Mrs. Andy W. Approaches us in a most rude manor and says yeah I'm watching you do this and that blah blah blah, well that was all I was going to take. I got my phone from my pocket and proceeded to take his photo for this purpose here. As soon as he realized I had taken his photo, he attempted to grab my phone from me while verbally assaulting me with profanity and threatening to call security. We were welcome to security as we had done absolutely nothing wrong. Both my wife as well as myself have never in our lives been treated with such blatant disrespect, humiliated, embarrassed, you name it, and that is how this Andy W. Completely ruined our shopping experience. Needless to say we left everything there, and drove across the street to Walmart where at least Ol Sam Walton has the since you hire employees who are not miserable in their own existence and in turn tries to bring everyone they come in contact with down and ruin their day. If possible I would have given zero stars. So though Meijer has completely alienated my family and I, Andy W. If you needed a hug all you had to do was ask.

The BEST sushi place I have ever been. Whenever Me and my husband are craving sushi we come here. My favorites are the highway 17 and the Sweetheart roll! Definitely recommend them! 


Me and my husband come so much that all the staff recognize and remember us and they make us feel so welcomed! We love it!

I only give a 1 star because that is the lowest acceptable. I stored my items for about 8 months while selling and purchasing a new home. What I found once I came for my items was an active water leak that districted nearly all of my families belongings. I did pull out a insurance policy but so much is irreplaceable. I filed a complaint with the district manager to be told there is nothing can be done about it. I thought being a reputable company and such a large chain that a problem like this wouldn't happen. I was sadly mistaken. I will encourage anyone to find a better storing facility and trust a company that has better business practices.

Excellent neighborhood Indian restaurant. We ate in their cozy clean dining room that had linen tablecloths and napkins. We had the Ekta Naan, Chicken Tikka Masala and the Ekta Tandoori and for dessert the Gulab jamun. Everything was delicious. Service was quick and pleasant. And the price was very reasonable. Quality all around. Highly recommend!
get greeted by name and shown the door with a hug when you leave.  Esther is mistress of her trade!

Went here for breakfast because it was in between my hotel and Broadway. Good food. Good biscuits. Good service. I was drinking a lot of water and the server filled my cup up over 10 times so that was very nice.
After posting my review, I got a message from the owner. He wanted to know more about my experience and I am confident that he genuinely wants to remedy any issues. Mucho respect, thus the 4 stars!

My boss from work had treated my co-workers and I for some cupcakes. My friend and I were in charge of getting the cupcakes since we drive to IUPUI for class and the bakery was close by. I really didn't know what I was expecting, especially since I have never heard of this bakery but I was very pleased.
When we got there, it was easy to find, it was noticeable. The bakery was little but too cute. We had a dozen to order and I didn't call ahead, we were afraid there wouldn't be enough. Needless to say, there was enough and plenty of choices to choose from.
The lady behind the counter was very nice and patient with us. We took a while to decide what all we needed. Would definitely come back. The place is great to go grab a cupcake, sit down and relax. Once all my co-workers received their cupcakes, everyone loved them! No one complained that it was too sweet or anything. Just the right kind of cupcake.

Peddler's village is essentially an outdoor mall located in bucks county. We decided to go up for the day this past Saturday. 

We've been here a few times over the years and have never really left disappointed. First off the parking stinks, they do offer a lot but it's mostly on the grassy area. There are a ton of restaurants and shops. This time of year they have the scarecrow festival which is nice. We will continue to come here to enjoy a nice day out.

Not sure what all of the rave reviews are about based on the experience we had last night. We have been wanting to try this restaurant for a while and finally decided to go on a special occasion. While everything tasted OK it seems to lack value for what you pay for, starting with the $8 domestic draft beer. A bit pricey. I ordered the Surf and Turf which definitely was not worth $30! I ordered my sirloin medium and it came back literally charred. The side of mashed potatoes was unflavored and came in a cupcake sized bowl. I got 3 medium sized prawns with the dish, nothing spectacular here. I also ordered a salad (extra charge) with dressing but it came back dry, with no dressing. Had to flag down the waiter for that. Our tab was over $250 for the six of us, which I more than expected and was willing to pay, but what we received in return was lackluster and not impressive at all. 5 star pricing for a 3 star meal. Sure, the place was packed, and I'm sure there are merits where it's due....we just didn't see what all the rave was about. Very disappointed. We'll go to Ruby River next time.

Ok, had dinner here the other day and was blown away. And it wasn't just the perfect  Long Island Ice Tea. Tried the Chicken Scaloppini. LOVED IT! Had way too much to eat, so took half home. But I think it was the best thing I've had here. Maybe. I really love their chopped liver too. And the lox...

Geez, too hard to say what's best, but I know I love the food here!! It's definitely worth 5 stars!!

I've eaten here twice with one time being a delivery and have been very satisfied both times. The snowbird dumplings are excellent and their curry had just the right mix of sweet and spicy. The wait staff is very courteous and the restaurant was nice and clean with a quiet dining room. Only critique I would have is a more imaginative selection of adult beverages but that is a minor detail.
Amazing meal. Had the specials asparagus soup. Scallops seared to perfection with roasted eggplant and fava bean purée. Delicious.
Great service and yummy food! The bread basket was very fresh as well. Sitting at an outside table was perfect and we were able to hear the music playing down the street in front of the Granada.

This is a simple review. 5 stars on beer and 5 stars on the great space. These guys are focusing on making an amazing product and it shows. Had a great time at this brewery and would highly recommend it if you are in town visiting and you want to meet some local beer folks.

This dealership is fraud.
I've not purchased any car, but used  to get my Lancer (in warranty) serviced from there.
Lancer owner's manual says change oil after 6 months or 7500 miles.
These scoundrels pasted a sticker and asked me to change the oil at 4000miles, what a scam. When confronted the SA tells me, oh this is because of NJ weather. I was like...LOL ! I've noticed them ripping other customers. These guys were my motivation to trade in my car for another Make. I would never recommend this place.
Plus there customer service waiting area sucks. Pathetic torn chairs, no coffee machine,  congested area, no Wi-fi. Mitsu of turnersville is much better.

I love Sunflower Market and especially thus location. This location seemed to offer a few more vegan items than the Speedway store. In general, they offer options from vegans and non vegans. A nice selection of wines to choose from.
The fresh produce is always VERY fresh!
Wish I lived closer to this location.

If you are looking for a low carb or healthier dessert option, look no further! This place is so underground and underrated. Their soft serve is one of the best healthy dessert options hands down. 
My usual order is a small cup, occasionally I'll order a medium. They rotate flavors often so there is always something different to try. Their ice cream flavors are mild (some more than others), never overly sweet. Some flavors can be somewhat similar but I honestly don't mind at all. They sell prepackaged to-go containers of their soft serve in various sizes as well as tons of low carb products. 
Due to covid, no samples are being served. They also have restricted indoor seating. They do, however, have a couple tables and chairs set up right outside.

You really can't beat $3.50 movies, and then $1.50 on Tues nights. Its as cheap as renting, if not cheaper and you get to watch it on a bigger screen. This site has a nice big parking lot and most people arrive 5 min before the movie or during the trailers... there is always room

Summerdale does the best custom work I've ever had! They're very exquisite when it comes to design and they pay attention to every small detail! You will not leave this place disappointed! They have been on Frankford avenue forever and they have tons of fabric to choose from! Great place if you want beautiful custom window treatments, upholstery, etc.

Would not recommend. Movie theater is dirty and the "leather" on the seats are all pealing. Service is not that good and food is nothing like what it looks like online or the menu. It has bad service and staff is unhappy.

I'm a Fan!  Went to the Phoenixville Farmers' Market yesterday.  I have to admit that I rate it a 3 rather than a 4 because I went late and it really didn't knock my socks off.  I am still a fan though.

The Market has relocated to under the Gay Street Bridge, so it is in a nice shady area.  Not as much fruits as vegetables as I thought they'd have, but again it might have been because of the time.  We did buy some tomatoes, red onions, and cucumbers.  The pricing was right and the flavors turned out fantastic. 

Tasted, then bought, some wonderful blue cheese from Birchrun Hills Farms.  They had some other very flavorful cheeses as well.  Will have to go back and try and buy some others.

Bought some fresh honey as well.  

Lots of good things.  Well worth a visit.  Pork, bison, veal, chicken and fresh eggs.  You also have to try some of the baked goods.

May be moving up to a 4 after the next visit.  Back next weekend for some more veggies.
I was so happy I found Gavas! I had a dress that was very large on top and Gloria fixed it for me. It was affordable and she was able to do it in the timeframe I needed! Highly recommend

Oh my goodness their Mac and cheese is to die for. Tried it for the first time today since they "popped up" at our office building. I expected plain Mac and cheese but it was soo much better then Mac and cheese. I also got their chicken tenders and the biscuit. Equally good!

My friends and I visited the seven stars inn after hearing great reviews from my colleagues.  I ordered the Prime Rib, which was not only huge but full of flavor.  This place is not cheap by any means, but for the quality and portion sizes along with the complimentary salads, it is well worth it.  The service was also top-notch and friendly as our drinks were kept full at all times.  We cant wait to go back again so I can try the Filet and Lobster Duet that I was told was also wonderful.

I recently discovered this place and it has quickly become my go-to for healthy food.  Highly recommend the teriyaki chicken bowl or the spicy garlic chicken bowl (it's not too spicy).  Jay, who works at the front, always gives really good service as well.

I love this little place! It is just so cute. I had coffee, beignets and orange juice. I felt like I was in Paris sitting here sipping on my coffee au lait. The beignets were better here than cafe du monde bc it's less dense, it's crispy here. However the coffee is much better at cafe du monde. I guess we just can't have it all! :( 

The music transformed the place into a hidden gem !

I have never had a bad experience at this Starbucks! I come here intermittently when my local coffee shop is unavailable. In all my years living in the area, the staff have always been extremely friendly and efficient. The location itself is clean and cozy, I love the sitting area for studying when I was in school. Only complaint is the location is hard to access due to no street parking surrounding the building, as well as being situated right along the bridge. I will continue to patriotism this shop!

Ok so I am giving it five stars because I am going to overlook one thing that I often ding other places on. Good luck getting a table. Why? Cause I have never gone here when there wasn't a 30+ minute wait. More often it is somewhere in the order of 45+ minute wait. But if you can go when it's not packed, get there early or figure a way to avoid the wait it is well worth it.

First it is styled after an Old Speak Easy. If you can't appreciate that then stop reading this. I don't want your eyes tainting my review. I mean they bring your check to you in a book. How cool is that?!

This is not a bar to go to pick some one up. Rather after you picked them up and decide calling them the next weekend take them here. 

The service has been great. The cocktails are really unique and the reason you came here in the first place. Expensive for Nashville yes but well worth it. And even though they don't taste strong, if you have more than one or two you will be feeling it.

Food is great but it is just appetizers, not dinner. It is just meant to be something to munch on while you sip your drink and catch up.

A must visit if you are in Nashville.

I believe I can sum up dinner at Stella Rossa's with one word - horrible.  Between the food, the incompetent bartender and the arrogant attitude of the staff from hostess, to the wait staff (Dominque) and ultimately the manager (Lesley) there is nothing to recommend this establishment.   You would do better buying a Stouffer's frozen dinner.

The night started badly when our party arrived at 5:30 pm on a Sunday.  There were many open tables and the hostess attempted to seat us at the one closest to the door.  When we asked for one of the open booths away from the door, she attempted to seat our party at the booth in the doorway.  Finally on the third attempt, the clearly irritated hostess seated us away from the door.

With the arrival, we were informed that the olive appetizer was not available, nor were they able to make their signature Blood Orange mojito.   When one of our party inquired whether the bartender could make an Italian spritzer, we were told he could.  However what arrived was not an Italian spritzer, but a watered down version of what he thought was the drink (our waitress later informed us he looked it up on the Internet).  When Lesley inquired what happened and was informed of the problem, she sullenly took the drink back to the bar and when she returned it was with a repeat of the same.  When the client informed her again what was wrong with it and how to properly make it, she argued with him.  

Things got progressively worse with the entrees.  My Caesar salad was the worst I've ever had (even hotel room service Caesar salads are better).  There were only a few croutons, the dressing tasted foul and the cheese resembled Parmesan, but only in passing.  Lesley was clearly irritated when I told her the salad was inedible and she walked away without even so much as an apology.  From then on we were marked as a "problem" and our service became agonizingly slow to non-existent.

My wife's chicken piccata was a simply grilled, tough chicken breast slapped on top of a few strands of linguine and topped with parsley butter and a squeeze of lemon on top and 6 capers; another inedible dish.

Finally in an effort to recapture the evening, the ladies tried to order wine, but when it finally arrived at the table after a 20-minute wait, it was the wrong wine.  At this point, we asked for the check, which came in at a whopping $101 for drinks, appetizers and entrees for a party of four.   There was no apology offered, no attempt to make things right, just an attitude that the staff thought this was our problem and not theirs.  Lesley even laughed at us, and the table next door who also sent back their entrees.  

So in short, besides the presence of good friends, the only thing that redeemed this night was the dessert we had at the frozen yogurt place down the street!

I went to the Fenway Rooftop Bar Sunday afternoon at 2 pm. The Rooftop Bar was not crowded at all. Two bartenders on staff. After I joined friends at a table I waited 20 minutes for someone to come over and take my order. We had a party at 4. It took another 10 minutes to get my drink. The server put down no napkin, no coaster. Condensation from the glass dripped all over me every time I took a sip. Service  declined from there. We had to bus our own table. The computers were down and we were told they could keep our credit card on file and email a receipt. I smell fraud all over that. We broke down our check and paid cash. Spectacular View.

This place is simple AMAZING! I was in the area and googled a brunch place and Turning Point popped up. The food was great, the ambience is welcoming and the staff was friendly. I'll definitely be back!

My husband and I stopped in to try some juices the Saturday after thanksgiving - a little detox. We split a flight of Neon Nectar, Detox Dream, Hoosier Heater, and the Garden. They were all fresh and delicious. We also split a lovely dill chicken salad sandwich. It was made with Greek yogurt - which is how I make mine. I was thrilled to see someone else using healthy and clean ingredients in their dishes. We're looking forward to going back!
Professional job and not too long of a wait. Even found stuff that I didn't realize went missing under my seat! I'm very picky when it comes to this stuff too, so I was pleased!
We order ice cream from this location occasionally through SkipTheDishes, and it can be very hit or miss. Sometimes they cheap out on the mix-ins, other times they get it perfect.

Went there once, food was good drinks were good, but the atmosphere needs work.  They could do so much more with the outside, I would complete close it off so the road can't be seen, pt lots of tropical plants and trees and string lights across the top.. The inside needs work also, to dark and old looking, make the inside modern...
This place is AMAZING! The food is superb, the staff members are kind and helpful, and the decor is rustic and beautiful. Definitely a gem of a restaurant!
This place is definitely a taste of Louisiana.   Good is great.  Service is great.   Recommend the Cajun Mary, a great bloody mary.
Absolutely delicious! Olio gave my husband and I the best restaurant experience we've had in years.

Clean and friendly spot with healthy servings of fish/rice poke bowls. If you've never had a poke bowl, try it. I was a fish butcher and when we got sushi grade tuna we'd put a little Ponzu and hijiki seaweed; small-time poke. The tuna here matches my expectations, a hard feat for TN. The price point is high but so is the quality and quantity. You get A LOT, it's also fresher and less heavy than pretty much everything else in 5 points. You can get other things than tuna, that's just what I like. Fire Mountain if you like spicy. You can customize pretty readily. They also have smoothies but I'm making another trip to try those.

My daughters and I have been to Dolce Vita a handful of times and have always enjoyed it but their business practices need a ton of work. We went in for Relaxation massages previously in March, when they had their "soft opening " and had no amenities available-not even robes and still charged full price!   We still enjoyed it and immediately rebooked for May.  AFTER our May massages I was shocked when I realized the prices jumped 25% with no mention of the price increase ahead of time. A business has every right to increase prices but at least have the common courtesy to inform customers so they can make informed decisions.  Because of this I have canceled our upcoming massages and will not return.  They are a large business and won't miss the three of us but beware

Compared to other hotpot places it is much nicer and cleaner here. There is also lots of space to get food as it is laid out buffet style. The only food you don't get yourself is the meat which you order on a form. This is likely to prevent wastage.

Just remember that any of the raw food you see available needs to be cooked! There are some pre-cooked items and that should be very obvious (fried chicken, spring rolls, green onion cake, and salads). Otherwise everything else you will cook in your pot of soup.

When you first arrive it can be overwhelming. Remember to choose a soup base, then get your sauces. The sauces add flavour to what you are cooking. Next get items you want to eat such as seafood, smashed meat balls or fish, veggies, noodles etc. Make sure the soup is boiling before you start throwing things into your hot pot! Try to keep one pair of chop sticks for raw and one for eating. Lastly I typically eat the noodles last as that is most definitely a finisher!

Just ridiculous the amount of time you have to wait in line. There is never enough cashiers. Well, there is, they are standing around up front talking to each other or complaining about their jobs or on thier cell phones. I have used the pharmacy and they have complained right in front of me! Managers have even complained! I'm making the drive to Deptford Walmart from now on.

Chris Whitney: The best realtor I have worked with.
Knowledgeable: Knows the area & the market - accurate & timely responses to the numerous questions that come w/ a home sale/purchase.
Loyal: Works tirelessly to ensure the customer gets exactly what they want in a home.  Always has his customers best interest at heart.
Results: Will do whatever it takes to get the sale finalized.  A true professional - I was lucky to have him on my side!!!

Jim Wilson
1st Sgt USMC (ret)

This is my FAVORITE Mediterranean spot in the city. Always consistent and delicious. I get the Chicken Shawarma platter or the Chicken Kebabs and am always happy! The Jordan almonds at the end of a meal is a nice touch. It's just good. You should go!

I'm not sure if the employees just hated their job and/or were just having a bad day. Mumbled a lot over the counters, kept asking "and next" before I had time to process what I wanted. Just overall impatient. I got the turkey breast on a 6" and 4 teeny pieces of meat were put on the bread.. usually they do a great job of adding a proper amount of meat. I asked if I could have more slices and he said for an extra charge... yeah okay. Both employees proceeded to not say thank you or have a good day and really just made me feel like a piece of shit for ordering from subway. I know it's a chain and all, but some good customer service goes a long way.
