I was looking for a pedicure place near where I live that I could just drop into to get my nails taken care of.  This turned out to be not that place.  When I arrived no one came over to greet me and find out what I wanted. Someone did yell from across the room. (!) The girl that was assigned to me was long and lanky and I think she will have back problems from her job before she turns 30.  She sort of worked on my feet while she was finishing up another customer.  I was concerned about the cleanliness of the establishment. The foot bath seemed ok as I watched them clean others around me. The tools however were suspect in my mind because they were brought in from a back room and did look used. At the end of her work on my feet the tech had some kind of attack. I believe it was from the fumes of the products she was using. She ran outside.  I will try another place next time.

Ruth Chris is exactly what you would expect from a high end steakhouse. The quality of food and level of service are superb. The atmosphere is dark, sultry and sophisticated. Being there makes me feel good. 

I came in strictly for their swizzle and stir happy hour which runs from 4 until 7. They offer drinks for $9.00 and they have food for $9.00. You'll find a burger, steak sandwich and chicken sandwich with fries. Crab beignets, shrimp and tuna are on the menu too. You can't beat this deal.

A piano was playing in the bar which I really enjoyed.  It enhanced the overall experience.

This is kind of a neat Place. Recently I've seen a bunch of new clean eating places pop up all over the place in the general rule of thumb is if you sell enough quinoa and rice and have food that is either organic or grass-fed you can call yourself clean eating. I don't really care it was freaking delicious.

It's more of a bowl place but you can also get some sandwiches there too. Generally you get a rice or quinoa choice and then you get a protein and then you can top it with stuff. I went crazy and chose the BLT wrap which was a hot and press trap that did not seem filled with anything unnecessary. It had lots of bacon lettuce tomato and actually had beans inside of it to which or something a little bit different.

I did decide to get french fries here because I have not had french fries all week and I figured I would be bad for a little while. French fries are actually pretty darn good. They also had six different teas that you could get and your drink would come with or without ice. The drinks are already pre refrigerated I really don't think you needed ice as a watered them down they seem kind of watery enough anyway. I tried the passion fruit tea I'm not sure if there's actually tea in it that it tasted really good and was not sugary at all and was a very light and refreshing drink. The rest of my group had bowls of some sort and I didn't hear a complaint from any one of them. I hope this trend keeps growing cuz it was 12 bucks for lunch it was actually pretty cheap and what I think good for you.

I'd say 3.5 for this spot. 

The restaurant is along Waters with a lot of good competition. Easy to find and park for, a nice indoor space and layout. We were seated right away and given water. A server checked on us a few times before we were ready to order. Throughout the meal our waters were always full and plates cleared quickly. 

I was excited to try the potato cakes to start. The flavors were good and there were tasty accompanying sauces, I just wished the texture was firmer and crispier.  The chick peas were good though and cooked well.  One of the sauces had a little heat which gave the dish some extra kick. 

We ordered the bread basket which had a variety of Naan but was pricey for what it turned out to be. Another dish that fell flat was chicken that lacked flavor despite the sauce coating and was on the drier side.

Lastly we had the lamb vindaloo. This dish had a nice flavor, the chunks of lamb were plentiful. I really liked the rice and appreciated the cloves found in the rice to give a nice aroma and spice. 

We had asked for sauces on the side and highly recommend doing so!  We got a very nice cilantro yogurt sauce and a spicy tamarind and pepper sauce. 

Overall it was a good meal but a bit on the pricier side considering the location, atmosphere and dishes.

Excellent food and a beautiful atmosphere.  We came here as a family for multiple birthdays celebrated at once and it was just perfect.  We had an amazing time and the servers were awesome.  I highly recommend this wonderful restaurant to all family and friends.
Big portions and good food. Roasted corn grits and BBQ chicken - yum

Always friendly, reliable service and consistent quality.
Can't beat pizza when you just want the night off in the kitchen and bring a huge smile on my husband's lips!,

We typically get 4 toppings: salami, garlic, olives and shrooms. Simple and good!!

For a laundromat, it doesn't get much better than this. It always annoys me having to carry around quarters to do my laundry. It's 2014 for freaks sake! 
Although it costs $1 to purchase the card, you can upload money via debit or credit card which is a huge plus to me. I did a load of laundry for less than $4.00, I think it was $3.50 the other day. 1st 10 minutes of dryer is free ! 
The dryers are also really strong, meaning it takes way less time than usual for me to finish all my laundry. And time is money :)
If you don't have a laundry machine on your premises and this is in your area, highly recommended.

I came here after a long day and I am so glad I did. The food was so tasty, I especially loved the Lo Mein noodles. The environment was really cute too I would even come here for a first date. My server Jule was so nice to me and made sure I had everything I needed from beginning until the end. She made my experience here really special. I will be ordering take out and dining in again in the near future.

We went for lunch yesterday. Servers are aloof and not helpful. We stood in front of the hostess station for 8 minutes before we were recognized, the staff walked past us several times. They aren't even good servers! Its not that great restaurant! I don't understand where the attitude comes from. 

We passed on the buffet, because it didn't look that great, plus I don't really go for buffet style. 

I ordered a bento box, the Basil Chicken was amazing. The pad thai tasted like Chef Boyardee spaghetti-os. 

After dropping off our tab, the server bailed out for another 20 minutes. Its lunch! People are in a hurry! Why would you do that?!

And its overpriced.

Went on opening day and I must say that I am BEYOND thrilled about it's new presence in the area. I've eaten at Cheesecake Factory many times before, but this is the first Cheesecake Factory in the tri-state area (Mississippi, Alabama, Louisiana). It's in a great location and the dining room is bigger than many other CFs I've been to. As always, the menu selection was amazing and the food that was ordered was flavorful and nicely presented (Dynamite Shrimp, Buffalo Blasts, Greek Salad, Chile Rillenos). Id also add that the service was exactly what I expected: phenomenal. Cheesecake Factory attracts a certain clientele that is sure to really make the area flourish. I really hope this resturant does well and I hope it continues it's success!

Don't let the word "budget" scare you away. You may be thinking that this place is where crackheads go, but nope. It's way cleaner than chains I've been to, and the staff is really friendly. The cont. breakfast is cute(it's the usual stuff - if you want eggs and bacon go to Denny's!!) and the pool is clean. I would totally stay here again, and am stoked  that we stumbled upon this place. Got microwaves and fridges in the rooms and king size beds that are comfy. AC works great and it's clean without having to burn your nose hairs from a bleach smell. Carpets look great and I head they have pet rooms available for those that travel with animals-I don't. 
 
Work checking out we paid less than 70bucks for a night :)
Stopped in after I was treated so rudely at Julie's Nails in same plaza. Ladies were lovely! Thoroughly enjoyed my pedicure!!

Hands down, the best Mexican food outside of Mexico. Best service, clean friendly atmosphere. Food is fresh, delicious, and perfectly prepared. Their in-house hot sauce is a symphony for your mouth. The carnitas, steak, & grilled chicken are all amazing. Sopes, tacos, nachos, and best of all - homemade flan - YUMMY! I ate at the Malvern location. There are several other locations, but I haven't tried them.

Yummmm classic Italian and finished the Neal with mama maria herself! I had the caprese salad and a side of homemade meatballs..some of the best I've had. A plate of mixed veggie appetizers was brought out complimentary and it was all so tasty! I had a bite of the melon and prosciutto and that was the best I have had for sure..love finding these little gems when I travel!

I like this Kroger. It's in a great location that needed some love. And it's always busy, so that says something. 

I love the natural foods section. I love Whole Foods but live way too far from it for a quick stop...this little section has everything I need, even bulk foods. Except sometimes I forget its there and when I look for my favorite brands in other parts of the store and can't find them, I get mad (my fault!). 

As far as grocery stores go, it's definitely a larger, cleaner, and brighter. Same Kroger pricing as any other store. 

The only thing that bothers me is the produce. I am a big fruit and veg girl and I am often underwhelmed by the produce. For example, I've tried (and failed) several times to get avocados from this location. I've never come home with any that were that great. Typically, I have to run over to Fresh Market, where I am guaranteed a good produce experience. On the other hand, I do get some produce (blueberries, already cut pineapple, strawberries, onions, etc.) that is perfectly fine for WAY cheaper than Fresh Market. So, it all evens out in the end, I guess. And I can get 10 Fage greek yogurts for $10 at Kroger. Definitely can't do that at Fresh Market.

I received excellent take out service by a warm, friendly and efficient staff. I stopped in a a particularly busy weekend for Corner Cafe Bakery. While I was very happy to see they were busy I was saddened that they had updated the menu and removed some solid vegan options like the quinoa salad and a vegan soup they previously offered. In addition my beloved oatmeal date cookie was gone an replace by the standard combination of oatmeal raisin. Say it ain't so! 

The special seasonal Maple Pecan Pumpkin Baby Bundt I purchased was as great if not better than it looked. It was simply delightful. I was happy to find a pumpkin selection well after Thanksgiving and, on top of that, it was delicious. 

I still love the place and the staff is great however I am sadden by these recent developments. I know a change is a part of life but whyyyyy remove the good stuff? :)
Had my daughters Quinceañera cake made here and I was amazed at the design. I will be returning.

The best Veal Parmigiana in our city, without contest. Maria (owner), cuts her own cutlets for the Parmigiana and makes sauce twice a day. It is a place we go to for Italian food when we are homesick. The calamari is definitely worth it, we ask for red sauce on the side. The buns are crusty and soft on the inside and the house red is a perfect dry Italian. Go now, go lots!
Awesome chicken... in fact, the best freaken chicken ever. People there are genuinely friendly and.. oh... did I mention the chicken was good :-D

I eat at this location quite a bit. It's the half way point to my destination Fresno to Boise and vice versa. They are always busy, always! Ordering quickly is never a problem. Wait time is a bit longer than I would like but it's not that long really. It's usually less than 8 mins but smelling the food makes it seem longer. I always order the same thing every time, 2 double doubles, with extra veggies, with both versions of grilled onions, chopped and whole, with grilled chills thrown into the sauce and extra sauce with both chopped. Then an order of fries, well done, animal style, with grilled chopped chili also. This place never disappoints me. Parking can be a battle but I usually have to get gas anyways so I fill up next door at the 7 eleven and just leave my car at the pump with the pump still in it. It's a big gas station so it's not like I'm blocking business so I don't feel bad.

I brought my puppy in for Miss Vanessa's six-week beginner course, and I was very happy with the results! Vanessa helped me feel like a good pet-mom, and explained that bribing my puppy to get results was okay. She took the guilt out of training, and showed how to use positive reinforcement. Vanessa is kind, soft-spoken, strong when she needs to be, and obviously loves dogs. My puppy will definitely be joining the intermediate class.

This is as good as it gets for big shows coming through Tucson.  Recently attended shows include Spoon, Interpol, The Smashing Pumpkins, The Avett Brothers and Edward Sharpe. Simple interior gets out of the way of the bands. There are better places to go in Tucson for a good live show that won't cost 30 bucks, but for the major events there's only one destination. Highly recommended.

Fast and friendly service!! Excellent chocolate cake and a nice place to go mid afternoon for a drink.
There's lots to choose from in frozen drink selection.

So I'm in the line at this Dunkin and I'm only the second car.  It's taken forever.   It's my only day off and I when I finally get to the window, the woman apologies and hands me my coffee.  NO CHARGE and apologizes for the wait.    She made my day.  Customer service lives.   THANK YOU.   Ill go out of my way to visit this location again.

Stupid Yelp app! I accidentally hit 1 star when I was just looking up info and can't readily discover how to remove it. So changing to 5 stars simply because I've heard good things and it's not fair to penalize the company for my mistake.

This primos was clean and nicely decorated. Lots of tables to eat there if you choose. I ordered the veggie diablo and the long hots included were super hot. i had to take some off at the end. it was very good.

500th review! I have to make it a good one, right? There was one special place that immediately came to mind...the spot I became a Mrs.! (This is less about the history/tours and geared mainly towards future brides/grooms or anyone planning a special day/photos here).

Our dream wedding location was the gorgeous, regal, historic gazebo at Fairmount Water Works. For us, it was THE perfect ceremony spot. This beautiful structure overlooking the river, nestled between Kelly Drive and Boathouse Row, at the foothills of The Philadelphia Museum of Art, not far from the Azalea Gardens is very special to us... 

When we lived in the Fairmount/Art Museum area we took walks/jogs on the drive daily, ending here at the gazebo. One day, waaaay before we were engaged he said "wouldn't this be an amazing place to get married?" That's it! I was done! That's all I needed to hear! This was going to be THE spot one day!

-We wanted somewhere we could visit forever with our children and one day, with our grandchildren.

- We wanted someplace we would always have access to as we wished and a place we would be assured would never close. 

-We wanted somewhere with rich history and a place that held permanent residence in a city and neighborhood we loved so very much. 

-We wanted what so clearly was "our" spot. 

I jumped through many hoops to secure this location for us! He got down on one knee October 17th and I had to wait until January 2nd, which for an excited bride is an eternity!! 8am on the second freezing day of the new year, with a money order in hand as instructed, I was at the door of the Fairmount Park Commission up on Concourse Drive in Fairmount Park, diagonal from Please Touch Museum. There, I filled out an application and waited and waited....and waited, and yep, waited, all the way until spring hoping to finally get the thumbs up on approval!! (It was a very long winter that year haha) You see, they give first priority to charities and local organizations and won't schedule weddings/ceremonies on days when there is a regatta on the river. Being that our date 10-10-10 was oh so insanely popular to begin with, I had my doubts we would even get it even if there weren't events going on. I still kept the faith and we did get it!!! The notification that we did for sure secure the space was THE greatest news EVER! Actually, a real dream come true! Well worth the wait!! 

Important things to remember :

-The number to call for more information is: 
(215) 685-0060
$500 for the gazebo for 2 hrs $150/ hr for photos. (We never pay for photos. We're smart about the times we come ex: mid week, just before sunset. We haven't had an issue in 5 years) 

-you may not tie anything to, or alter the gazebo in any way. (We had a hand held chuppah.) 

-you will need to order your own chairs. The cost can be very minimal if you shop around a bit!

-you MUST have your permit for the space with you at all times! 

The most important part of my review however is this: NO ONE but the Fairmount Park Commission owns the gazebo and surrounding structures! PERIOD!!! If you google it, even go for a tour there, it would appear the restaurant which was then the Water Works (currently Cescaphe group) owns the gazebo. In fact, they will try to tell you you they own it! THEY DO NOT!! NEVER WILL!! This misrepresentation enrages me because it holds many couples and (almost) us from our dream wedding ceremony! We first hand went on a tour where we were told this. We already had our reception caterer booked elsewhere so we had no interest in the reception space. We were ALMOST conned as many are when looking into the gazebo and cocktail space! After a little investigating from an uber determined bride, we came to find that use of the gazebo comes only with reception booking was a lie!!! You do not need to use the restaurant to use the gazebo. If you simply want to rent the gazebo or any aspect of the Waterworks outdoor spaces, you can absolutely do this without booking the restaurant for your reception! We still run into many, many couples who look over the gazebo because one reason or another regarding the restaurant. Despite what it may seem, they are completely separate and always will be!! 

After moving from the area, we don't visit here daily anymore, but we absolutely continue to come each and every year for our anniversary. We play our wedding song, the kids run up and down what was our aisle, and of course, I cry! I LOVE looking through these photos of how our little family is growing year after year!

This is a truly beautiful, magical spot and we couldn't recommend it any more for a wedding ceremony or for special photos. The space is elegant and neutral, making for the ultimate perfect backdrop. It's definitely not an easy site to secure for ceremonies, but believe me, it's extremely well worth it!

This was quite an awesome eating experience.  Came here on a cold Friday night and it was the perfect place to warm up with fine cuisine and your own personal bottle of wine (BYOB!).  The food was classy, filling, creative but best of all, unpretentious.  The crowd was pleasant and service was outstanding.  

My favorite items:  The borscht and scallops were my top choices.  The menu changes all the time so just ask the server for their top recs, ours took interest in helping us choose.  For dessert, the beignets are a MUST.  They are made fresh and are just delectable.

I'm new to Nashville and I was very nervous about moving from Chicago and finding a hair colorist and stylist.  I love Parlour 3 and I have had just about every service done - color, cut, make-up and lash application, special occasion blow out, nails, waxing (brow and brazilian), and spray tan.  All have been great experiences, and professional ladies.  I have become a regular (and fan!) of Korie for my hair and I think she is as cute as they come.  Pleasure to chat with and knows her stuff.  She is also very into making sure you love what she's done before you leave and also very willing to help her clients into her tight schedule.  Thankful I found this place!

I was rear ended in a parking lot and took my car to VIP Collision Center. I also had some work that was outside of the accident done. Courteous, timely and good work.  They even washed and supplied me with a Covid Stimulus package (nice to get a present).  Thank you Alfred and Barbara.

I stumbled across this place at a food truck really. The owners are originally from New York and are very friendly. I ordered a hamburger empanada and it was very delicious. I'm already planning the next time to visit so I can try other items on the menu!!

I have been hearing great things about Paladar 511 for a few weeks now...so I decided to pop in and give them a try. 

Time of Visit: Saturday Night (9:45pm)

First things first...atmosphere. This restaurant has a vibrant vibe. The open kitchen is absolutely great to watch. All the chefs are working hard and focused. 

The food was awesome from start to finish. Yellowfin Tuna....pizza...ravioli...peach upside down cake. Flavor and presentation really pop. Many shareable plates and definitely affordable. They have tandem servers which were all helpful and genuine when it came to menu recommendations. 

An overall great experience. I will definitely add these guys to my restaurant rotation!

After a somewhat mediocre visit to the El Encanto for happy hour last week, yesterday we decided to go to the Plow and Angel with our friends! 

We arrived early knowing that spending a few minutes walking around the beautiful grounds is like walking around the Garden of Eden!  The first thing we noticed when we pulled up is that the valet was friendly and welcoming!!!   Are you listening El Encanto?   We were lucky, yesterday was the most pleasant Santa Barbara day so far this year, what a great day to sit outside!  

The hostess and our server were wonderful!   Friendly and helpful.    The Plow and Angel has a real happy hour!   There are $3 beers, $5 well drinks ( I think their well has some pretty good quality to it) and a couple of wine and Martini specials.    For food they had about a dozen items on the menu.    I tried the fenole sausage pizza for $14.   Delicious!   The lamb sliders were a popular favorite as was the grilled artichoke with a great aioli sauce.   

An option if you are a little more on the hungry side is a three course pre-fixe menu for about $38.    We didn't know about it ahead of time so we didn't go for it.   Maybe next time. 

I would caution you that the "Angel Hour" is just that, an hour!    5pm-6pm.    I think that our server was a little generous in that her watch seemed to be running a little slow to our benefit!   

All-in we fell between $20 and $25 per.    Very reasonable considering the beautiful setting!!!     We will be back for sure!!!!

If I could give this place no stars I would, was craving seafood for my birthday on Thursday  so we went here. Took 5 mins to even be noticed when we walked in. Finally got sat and told our server would be right over! Sat at the table for a 25 minutes without anyone coming over to even greet us. There were 3 tables taken in the entire restaurant. Other wait staff looked at us numerous times and acted like we were invisible. Got up and finally walked out and went to a different restaurant. I would not go to this place ever again, worst service I have ever received.

Loop Found myself in the right part of town at the right time of day to follow friends' "must do" advice! Had to wait about 5-10 minutes outside (Yes, it's THAT popular!) but it was well worth it. 

Thank you, chefs! THAT'S what I imagine when someone says fried chicken and corn bread muffins!
appetizers were good.  Food was served cold.  We had to wait since the hotel was serving hotel guest first t.

This place is very popular. Always busy with lots of customers, and it's a good sign. The staff is very helpful and also very personable. Another good sign.

Since we started our moving process a few months ago to Reno, I've been frequenting this thrift shop. I never walk out empty handed! They have great variety of dishes (from single items to huge sets), furniture, household items, books, clothing, framed arts, and pet supply! I think especially the furniture inventory rotates pretty quickly, so check them out often.

I've gotten several great everyday-dishes and glassware. Baskets too. Some are brand-new with used prices. Given the fact that the proceeds from the sales are used for SPCA and their animals, there's no reason not to like this shop.

Ordered a 16 oz ribeye rare. Came out medium and tasteless. Chewy and just not good. Baked potato was small. The rice wasn't bad but I didn't go there for rice.
Idk what cut it was but it wasn't prime or select. I guess when you pay peanuts you get monkeys.
Won't go back.

I have seen Dr. Meller twice at the med center. I knew when it was him on duty I was wasting my time. I saw him Sunday the 12th of May was my second visit and nothing else was available. 

I knew I didn't want to go to the med center after my first visit with him. I went in with complaints of a sore throat, congestion, eyes red and itchy leaking all day. The pain in my throat would wake me up at night. He took down all my symptoms and told me to gargle aspirin and offered me nothing else. 

Right after I walked in another patient was complaining about Dr. Meller pushing him out of the officer. 

I went to my actual PCP on Monday because I couldn't go into work and he gave me a zpak and a medrol dosepak. Today, only 3 days into my zpak course I feel remarkably better. 

If you don't want to be a doctor and help people don't do it. But don't see people who are sick and make them feel like they are crazy for coming to a doctor for some relief. I knew before I got there they would charge my insurance and my copay and offer me nothing. I will never go back to any of the MedCenters. I hope they go out of business. Worst doctors in Santa Barbara and they can be that way because they are the only urgent care in town open on Sunday's.

I had to give 5 stars because of Loni. I went in for a massage. An amazing deal on Groupon. She was perfect! But it is a fitness center so the spa environment is lacking because it's not a spa. The temperature in the massage room could have been warmer and they should have some lemon or better yet cucumber water to offer before and after. That said I had a wonderful experience with Loni. I will be back.

Every time I go to the P&P, I wake up the next morning enveloped in regret. I should probably stop going, huh? 

It had been a long while since I set foot in the place. So long, in fact, that I was told the ground floor bar had been closed for renovations for some time and the bar action was now upstairs. 

The upstairs bar area looked like part of a sad comedy club from the early 80s. The only brightness in the room came from a small television, and the creepy monitor from the video camera trained on the front door. Absolutely no music played, and I didn't see or smell any hot water dogs. Downgrade.

My three stars are for the daydreams I have, thinking about what characters have sat at the bar over the years and wondering if they shared the same melancholic feelings as me while doing so. 

I hope not to return, but at some point I probably will.

This is without question the ONLY place you should eat Chinese in West Chester and the Sushi is equally amazing .......never once had a bad experience here .....I have read some other reviews about bad service and I just don't see it ......we go 4-5 times per month and never see anyone leaving unhappy ..I think some may have issue with the fact that many staff have English as a second language and confuse shyness or uneasiness with verbiage as rushed and unfriendly .........

This place is great...so relaxing..fish dishes so fresh...beer on tap ..cold..just had dinner with my wife..buffalo shrimp and crab  cake..very good..entrees..mahi mahi blackened and shrimp primavera..both awesome..key lime pie very good..prices very fair...service was great..thank you..

It is hard to believe that they have so many positive reviews. I brought in a jacket with worn and frayed trim at the bottom of the sleeves and asked to have it shortened so the trim would be removed. It took 3 weeks. They did not remove the worn out trim but shortened the sleeve from the middle instead of doing what I asked. They fixed it but now the sleeves are too short. When I picked up my jacket they practically threw it at me. I will NEVER go there again. Beware.

Italian. 

In a city with a number of good Italian restaurants on the hill, this is actually one of my favorites.  Probably because it's local to me, and because it's still classic Italian, with a contemporary atmosphere.

Classic Italian fare, tons of pasta dishes, plenty of sauces, veal, chicken, and other meats galore.  

It's price tag is on the higher side, but definitely worth it.  Excellent wine selection to go with any dish.

Definitely a special event location, like an anniversary, graduation, or birthday dinner.  

Service was excellent, and the server was very knowledgeable about the entire menu.

best. movie. experience. ever. 

you've got to come here for happy hour! 1/2

My wife and I were thinking of getting a used car when she went back to work from having our first child. We constantly hear the ads on the radio and see them on TV so we went to their site just to see prices and what they have. The only way to look at their site is to enter your phone number so we did. The next morning I got a call and the lady wanted us to come in but I told her we needed to wait until my wife got back to work but she didn't seem to understand this concept. I told her we would come in when my wife went back to work and we caught up on some bills. Over the next week I received 87 phone calls all with voice messages asking when we were going to come in and look also I have 43 text messages from her asking the same thing. If they're going to be this pushy I don't think we're coming to look.

I came here for my boyfriend's grandfather's birthday. We were seated in the event room. it was enough space for about 20-25 people with plenty of room for a few kids to move about. l had the fried chicken which was cooked well, the skin was crispy but not too greasy. i also had green beans for a side. it was ok. over all it was a good meal for me but nothing stood out. The service was excellent, i know how overwhelming it is to cater and serve many people and our servers did fine once all the drinks were brought out.
Friendliest drive thru employees ever. I love stopping through whenever I'm grocery shopping in Brentwood.

I liked the hot dogs and burger wasn't bad however it's nothing new. The vibe inside is different but that's about it different music makes you feel like your in the city of I'm guessing Chicago although the music sounded very Louisiana

I'm never disappointed when I come to Tierra. The portions are huge and the food always tasty. The service can be a bit slow once it's time for your check so don't go when you're in a rush. Some delicious plates I've had have been: avocado and mango salad with either chicken, churrasco steak or salmon (all delish), mofongo, sampler platter, Cuban sandwich, medianoche sandwich, garlic shrimp, churrasco/skirt steak with sides, fruit drinks, breakfast platters and more. Come with an appetite and be satisfied.

They don't have Comcast, so keep in mind if you're trying to watch Flyers for instance.

Staff were nice and attentive, they had a good selection of beers, but food didn't look like anything special. Not something I'd want to try for the first time before a long flight, put it that way.

this place has amazing reviews online so i went there last sunday to get my screen replaced. they said they had to special order it and that i had to put down a 50% deposit. did not hear from them for a week, called them this past sunday and they said they were "just about to call me" to tell me they had my screen. took my phone in yesterday for the replacement and when i came back an hour later (after they helped the customer who came in after me) told me they had a "hiccup" fixing my phone, in that, they broke the new screen. now they are waiting on another special ordered screen, but they go on vacation tomorrow.

so now my phone is extremely unresponsive when i'm trying to do stuff (not scrolling, selecting things i'm not holding down on, etc, etc), and the power is also draining extremely fast.  i have tried calling and they are not picking up their phone.

*edit: i eventually had to go to this place myself when they weren't answering, they gave me a free new phone in the hopes of turning my opinion about them around.*

Do not recommend, avoid this place at all costs.

This is sorry to say as I love Jerry Bobs. Today was BAD!!!  This location has been slowly declining for a few months and today I will not be back to this location. 32 min for drinks to show at table, took 18 min just to have our drink order taken. 23 minutes for food to come out and then my hash browns and wife's were cold also.  Poor drink service as my coffee was only refilled 3 times over a 45 min period. 

Love Jerry Bobs but will not be back to this location.

I know I shouldn't assume things because then I make an ass outta u n me , but the man who took my order wasn't remotely Indian - Pakistani - Bengali - anything close - 
I ordered butter chicken aka chefs special - it was done in 5 minutes which was a red flag - he asked, which level of spicy - I figured hot would make me choke so I said medium - 
It tasted like they put ketchup in there to tame the spice which I've seen done at a pizza shop before when hot wings were ordered - I instantly recognized the taste - 
The dish itself tasted like meatballs. 
I knew this was a toss up - but man I'm disappointed. 
But I paid 16 dollars for what actually tasted like a meatball bowl from wawa , if I was blindfolded I would have guessed that. Not to mention I it came with 1 small sized chicken breast cut up. 
The rice was fine but it's not that hard to make rice in the rick cooker.

Rating- 2.5
I first walked into Fuku my freshman year, and they gave me a menu pamphlet. Now, it's my senior year, and we finally decided to try the place. 

We ordered some delivery sushi along with the tofu noodle bowl. As you would expect, the sushi wasn't exactly cold and refreshing when it got to my front door. But, I'm not sure if that's reasonable to ask drivers to bring the food in an ice cooler...

The sushi menu was diverse, but a little too many "edgy" choices for me. But, I can understand the appeal. 

It was pretty irritating that there were no plastic bowls, or anything of the sort, for the soy sauce when the food arrived. Only soy sauce packets (more on that later). I mean, if you're going to deliver sushi, you should put some effort into making it a similar experience as it would've been in the restaurant. So, just be prepared to find some tiny bowls in your kitchen cabinet to use for soy sauce dipping.

Speaking of the soy sauce... what the hell? Just buy Kikkoman instead of the terrible tasting generic soy sauces you provided. It really took away from the sushi dish for me. Fuku.

The tofu noodles were more like "deconstructed noodles with a side of tofu and veggies drowned in ground black pepper". Not very good. 

In the end, the sushi itself was very good. I applaud the sushi chef. The soy sauce, the non-existent bowls, the noodles, the tofu, and the flavor were all meh and/or bleh.

Elements was great! I had the best hair cut and the best stylist. He was super friendly and cut my hair just the way I wanted. I hate having to cut my hair because it is so expensive (I have long and thick hair) so it was about $100 for cut and tip. The wash and dry felt so good and the cut was an appropriate amount of time!

The support staff is exceptionally rude told us at 4p
 That the museum was closed when we showed them a picture of their sign that the museum says 430p they statues yelling at us definitely would never go here again

We usually love this place, we've made it through the first few months waiting an hour for a table because the food and service was outstanding. But last Friday night ... They are starting to miss the little things.. First no one lite the candle on the table, the we had to ask for the wait staff to remove empty glasses, then app plates and finally dinner plates, largely due to the wait staff be fully engrossed with each other in conversation and not paying attention to the customer. We hate to see this and hope they start watching the little things that made us want to come back!

I have a cousin who's a YUGE Peyton Manning fan (she lives in the South) and she heard of Tow Yard's joint brew with Factotum (great name--Bukowski reference?) in Denver.    The cans are pretty cool and people are buying them as collector's items.   The beer is unlike any oatmeal beer I've had---it's a pale ale.

The food at Tow Yard is pretty standard pub fare.   We had the fried pickles and they were good.  I like the high ceilings and the industrial ambiance.  This would be a great space to host an event.  

The bartender, Angie, was very personable and good conversation.   The she was knowledgeable about the beers and ready with a suggestion or a taste! 

Indianapolis needs more places like this--raising both the beer and the coolness profile.

Went in last night for a sandwich after several of my friends have told me in the past how delicious this place is. Not sure what all the hype was about because I was not impressed at all. Sandwich wasn't good- the lettuce was bad, along with the tomatoes. Will not come back again.

I am absolutely addicted to the food here, well worth the wait for a table or even a seat at the counter. Our service here has always been top notch. They just recently updated the menu too, which was a pleasant surprise, adding some much loved specials to the regular menu.  A few of my all time faves are the pasole, biscuits and gravy, and the grits on fire. My husband and I always get a pancake with the house made sweet cream cheese butter to split. My husband likes the country fried steak or the egg sandwich.  I love that we can order our afternoon brunches with a fun Crispin Sunrise or Mimosa. Hands down my favorite brunch spot in St. Louis!!!

I moved to Philly in August and as much as I love to run/be outside for workouts, accepted that come the middle of summer and winter it's nice to escape indoors-however after going  to a couple spinning classes I am hooked regardless of temp outside!  

I happened to find this studio online-the website is great, extremely informative, and you can even sign up for class in advance online to reserve a bike, which is super convenient (no need to arrive early to "claim" a bike like other studios)! 

As far as the classes themselves-
The instructors are great- they help motivate/push you, have great energy all around-just down to earth good folks.  Not sure if anyone ever experienced a spinning class that drags on and the minutes tick by painfully slow...but this does NOT happen here!  Whether it's a 45 minute class or the hour-thirty, the instructors have great energy and the song choices are an awesome distraction-the beat matches up with the cadence to help you gauge how fast/slow you should be pedaling.  The playlists choices are great, and I often find myself downloading songs for my own ipod after hearing it there.  

About the studio: It's super clean, and has state of the art equipment.  The bikes are in great condition- the Keiser bikes they use are far better than the traditional spin bikes found in most other classes. 

Whether you are new to spinning or been cycling for years the instructors are extremely knowledgeable and happy to help set up bikes, watch your riding form, etc.  

All around, awesome workout experience-I look forward to going every week to get in a solid workout and having fun while I am there too. 

Wish I could give more that 5 stars!

I ordered from Uber last night. It was two slices of pizza in a styrofoam box left on my doorstep. They were cold and stuck together. It was potatoes and bacon. Not hardly any toppings. I called last night to let them know and manager hung up on me. Said he new my address and phone number. Said he was going to call the police. Haha. He said why would I complain about a measly 7 dollars. We with Uber eats it $20.00 dollars. What a creep. I called back 5 times. Every time I got hung up on. I'm going to call the owner on Tuesday. Hopefully they let this jerk go. He is so lucky to even have a job during the COVID. This was my first time ordering in this scary time and I ended up with a total jerk manager on the phone. I didn't want a refund. I just wanted to give him some advice that might make things better.  Hope they fire the manager

The place is inviting and the location is convienant! Try the Apple Strudel warmed with homemade whip cream! My favorite! Although I usually come to Andersen's for my pastries, i decided to try brunch. I'm glad I suggested the idea! Megan was incredible as a server, very attentive! I will be coming back for more!

I have higher expectation after viewing all the good reviews. But the food are not that tasty and the portion are small. They don't worth the money. We ordered chili wonton, pork soup dumpling, traditional pan fried bao and green onion oil dry noodles. The skin of the wontons and dumplings were too thick and doughy, tasted like frozen grocery products. They can definitely do better.

I really enjoyed my first foray into this store, even though I had a huge headache that day and was just killing time while I waited to go to my bridal appointment across the street. They have loads of great stuff here, and I loved the atmosphere. They also had Clarisonic skincare brushes IN STOCK. That is hard to come by. The girls were all friendly, helpful and informative. I could browse at my leisure or ask as many questions as I wanted. They also have a gift registry for weddings and showers. That is something that is good to know! I ended up leaving with a hand cream called Fluffy Bunny, and it is simply divine. I will be back to get more when it runs out (it smells like spearmint and lavendar for all those who get migraines. I love it. It doesn't bother my head).

Decent Thai food as a small quiet spot. You would totally miss it if your not looking close.

Attentive staff, quiet ambiance and decent food. I will def give some other dishes a try.

Don't judge a spot by its location!

We just got a New Mexican restaurant in Berwyn!    

They opened yesterday (8/2/15), and when I went in with hubby and kids yesterday we were the only customers.   

My husband had a chicken chimichanga, with black beans, rice and salsa inside, deep fried and a white sauce on top.   He said it was very good.  

I ordered a 'house platter ' - a choice of meat, with rice, beans and tortillas on the side.   I chose the pastor, a slightly sweet and well seasoned pork.   Not spicy, but very flavorful.   

My preschoolers each had a plate of rice and beans (their standard at Mexican restaurants), which they happily assembled into 'sandwiches' with my tortillas.   Some bites of the refried beans had a kick, but not all, so they almost needed a bit more stirring.   

The owners also made us a pretty complimentary plate of chips and salsa.  I liked them, my hubby would prefer more of a corn chip, but it was good.  

Overall food was very tasty.   Atmosphere is very casual - clean hole in the wall painted in bright colors with sombreros for decoration.     I would guess booths/tables might seat 30 total.    

Room for improvement (remember they've been open only a day): have cups/tap water available, hook in bathroom door for purse, and add plantains to the menu! 

We will definitely be back, and hope they get enough clientele to make it.
Oh my gosh. That meal was dynamite! Had chowder, chowder fries, the special lobster with chips, some fried pickles, and the surf and turf burger. I loved every single thing! So good. I'll be back

New restaurant in town and the better half wanted to give it a try. 
 A Cajun place is the first of its kind in this area, so our hopes were high. New Port Richey and Port Richey is where restaurants go to die, either from the staff or the unfair reviews from the locals. I have spent a great deal of time in Louisiana and Texas over the years, so I will try and be constructive.
 Interior: very clean and well lit. They have a nice mural over the central area, but the walls are painted white and the overall feel seems a bit more industrial. The best way to describe it is the nearby restaurant "Catches" you will know what I mean if you've been there. I would recommend a more nautical theme, such as fishing nets hanging on the wall etc..
 Our initial impression when walking in was a disinterested hostess who barely said a word. When walking out, not a word. Nothing. Very strange.
 Our waiter was Shawn. Great guy and very attentive.
   Now for the food: the menu had either fried or boiled choices, but the the pairings were odd. Sausage was ala carte, which was new to me. Usually Cajun places include sausage with everything. I would recommend having more than one seafood item per steam bag, along with sausage, corn and potato. Again, just a recommendation.
 I had the "Captains basket" with fried shrimp and clams.the breading seemed under cooked. Not soggy, but not crunchy. You got 4 shrimp and 5 clams with fries for $13.99. Glad I wasn't starving. The clam boil my wife got was awesome with plenty to eat and great flavors. That choice is the best, but again, Gould have another seafood choice paired with it  in the bag.
 Now for the prices: the price point seems a little high for the area, which will probably more negative reviews. People in this area will always look for freebies.
 Overall, I gave it 4 stars because the food is really good, your wait staff, like Shawn, are good at what they do and I really hope this place sticks around.
 I will most likely be back and try the boiled offerings.

It is on 22nd just east of Craycroft if you blink you miss it especially if you're not looking for it. It's closer to the Chase Bank on 22nd on the north side of 22nd. It has pretty ample parking space when you walk in you seat yourself at the first available table.  With that being said the seating is limited but it has tables, a few booths, and traditional bar seats. 

The service was good, the best thing was that I ordered a hot chocolate and they brought me water without even asking or making a face when my friend ordered coffee and requested a water as well. 

They have varied breakfast & lunch meals from traditional American to traditional Mexican. I selected a more traditional Mexican meal: two eggs made to order, refried beans, salsa, tortilla, and your choice of a corn or beef tamale. I ended up receiving the the beef tamale instead of the corn tamale but it was great and once the corn tamale came out I still preferred to beef one.

This place is where you should go treat yourself after hunkering down...you can even reserve a table in the outside eating area, which many places won't do. It is both casual and elegant and the food has not disappointed.  Order the Brussel Sprouts...they are delicious.  Good service and a overall happy vibe.

I've eaten at two of their three locations. This is by far the best breakfast place in New Orleans. They always have a long way but you can get put on the waitlist through yelp or on their website. You really can't go wrong in this spot.

My husband and I ate here a couple months ago when we first moved to Boise.  This is the place that now when we are in the mood for BBQ, we say 'it can't be worse than' or 'as long as it's not'.  But before I go into why we won't be going back to this place, I do want to say that the staff there was incredibly nice and they did a have good amount of people come in and order out while we were there, they also seemed short staffed. While we sat waiting for our food, one of the staff walked by a table where someone had spilled their drink and it had poured on to the floor. The glass and the soda was still there and the customer long gone. That spill remained our entire meal. I ordered the ribs and the GF Mac & Cheese (I am not GF by choice).  The Mac & Cheese is also vegan, leading to an unpalatable taste and texture. The flavor on the ribs tasted artificial to me, and I wondered if they used artificial smoke flavoring during preparation. My husband ordered a sandwich and the meat tasted old.

Worth the stop if you're in the area. Very relaxed space, super friendly staff and free samples!!! They have some bottled flavors for sale, but if you're getting a few why not just get a growler filled with the freshest they have on tap? I will definitely be frequenting this establishment once the weather warms up.

I love Panda Express!!! Just not this location at all!!! 
Always closes early!!!!!! Why????? So frustrating!!!! Been to this location multiple times over a years time now, because of its convenience, lobby is always closed early. The staff never acknowledges you when your at the locked door with the open sign on and still an hour till closing while there flooding the dining room floor with water. So when I go to order at the drive thru I'm told we have limited items and will not be making anymore due to closing soon. Which is still an hour away!!!!!!!!!! Never had fresh food at this location. Hard crunchy rice and old dried up orange chicken, it breaks my heart. Please stop closing early!!!! If your business hours are till 9:00pm or 10:00pm serve your customers till that time with quality food and service!!!!

I joined Lifetime a year ago and I am a total believer.
There are a few activities that can get pricey but the quality of what you're getting plus the convenience of having everything under one roof is worth it. Summer camp, pool, real kids activities, nutrition, outdoor clubs, spa and salon... there really isn't much that Lifetime doesn't do to give you a complete wellness experience and lifestyle.

I had carpal tunnel surgery on both the right and left hands 3 weeks apart.  The work I had done with Dr. Kaplan was wonderful.  For the most part the medical staff was great to deal with as well.  My only issue is that it has taken me more than a month to get the billing statement I need.  They are unresponsive to emails (their preferred method of requests) and voice mails.  I also had some issues getting anyone on the phone at the Avon office.  It is woefully understaffed.  I would recommend the Center for your surgery, you just have to be very persistent with the office staff to get what you need!

Recommended to my son when he needed a suit, I had been in a few times for shirts, sweaters.  The gentleman who waited on us was very helpful and professional.  A few things bothered me though.  All the suits were 70% off according to the signage and our salesperson, I looked at my sons bill and he got 65% off.  No idea why.  The pants needed to be hemmed and that was the only alteration, the salesman said 10 days to 2 weeks. I've had alterations before and this seems like a long time especially since we are not near any holidays or anything.  Lastly, when we went to pick up the suit they said "oh you didn't pay for alterations".  $22.  I ask why we weren't told initially, she didn't know why.  When I have been with my husband he has never paid to have the pants hemmed on a suit.  They have some sketchy business practices...beware.

Visited IceBurg since I was in the area and it came up as "hot and new" on Yelp. This is my second time having rolled ice cream, the first being at Icesmile. I'm not sure if I'm just not a fan of IceBurg or if the rolled ice cream here just isn't right. You order and pay at the register then pick up your order near the back. For $7, there are pre-selected specials they offer, or you can create your own. 

I ordered a green tea ice rolled ice cream with oreo topping. The rolled ice cream here is super frozen. I think the settings on the plate where the ice cream was rolled were off because the guy who was mixing struggled with it. It was also very tough when I ate it. I heard one of the employees saying the ice cream is vanilla based then saw her mix green tea powder with the ice cream mixture. The rolled ice cream did not end up tasting like green tea at all. It was vanilla ice cream with a light green color. 

Judging from the pictures, it also looks like there's inconsistency to how many rolls you get per cup. There was a space in my cup that could fit another roll, but that's where the piece of Oreo and utensils ended up sitting. Overall, I would not order the rolled ice cream again here but instead, opt for an acai bowl. Hopefully, that would taste better and have a better texture.

Ohhhh hunny! I have finally found BBQ worthy of praise. I have been in the hunt for some really good and authentic BBQ here in Tucson and I have found them. I dragged my husband down to the Geico parking lot where they were situated for the lunch rush. We ordered the ribs dinner, a ribs only plate and smothered fries. The ribs had a rub that we had not tasted anywhere and were cooked perfectly. I still drool when I think about them. The fries were smothered in cheese, jalapeños, green onion and brisket. It's an extra $2 for brisket but is definitely worth it. I was also excited to see they had peach cobbler on their menu but sadly they did not have any on hand when we went. So I will go back once they open their restaurant on 22nd and stuff my face with cobbler and more BBQ. The employees were very down-to-earth and sweet. The food smelled so heavenly that we could not wait til we got home to eat so we ate right in the car in the Walmart parking lot across the street. I stand tall with BBQ sauce on my face and sticky fingers to say that I have zero shame for eating in the car. Their food is worth it!

I wish I had something positive to say but there's nothing. Literally I have never met an owner so dishonest and deceptive is DISGUSTING!!! Our initial re-pipe of our home was fine for the most part. When it came time to install our bathroom we ran into major issues. The team arrived and took 2 hours to install our tub faucet and shower head. We have an unusual faucet so we didn't think much of it. The team took a lunch break returned around 1:30 only to spend two hours sitting in their van on their phones. They came in once or twice mentioned they needed to figure out the sink pipes but didn't mention any other issues. When 4pm came to leave we still had no toilet installed and no sink. (Mind you we had company coming that weekend and we have 1 bathroom in our home- HUGE issue) the worker wanted to bill us for 10am-4pm - 6 hours of work at $134 an hour!!!!! my husband argued about how they sat in their car so they comped 1 hour. BTW in case you your wondering we paid for their 1.5 break!!!!! Yea we paid $200 for them to take their lunch break AND we paid for them to sit in their Van. When we brought up the sitting in the van he explained they where trouble shooting the issue of the sink. Sooooo here is the big issue they installed 3/4 pipes into our wall (that was now tiled) when we have 1/2" sink mount. THIS WAS THEIR ERROR!!!! We had the faucet present at the re-pipe installation. Our GC literally told them the parts they needed to adapt the two together and yet they sat in their van rather than going to the store to get the parts!!! They explained that the reason they couldn't install the toilet was because they didn't have the "upunor" (pex-a) tool to install it. IM SORRY!!! BUT WHAT PROFESSIONAL SHOWS UP TO A JOB WITHOUT THE TOOLS TO COMPLETE IT AND THEN BILLS YOU HOURLY!!!???  The toilet was present at the re-pipe so they had ZERO excuse for it not being prepared. This is the shadiest business we have ever worked with. So when my husband finally spoke to a area manage he apologized and came Saturday morning to install our toilet at no cost. That we greatly apupreciated. NOW to deal with the wrong pipes in the wall. My husband spoke to the owner who proceeded to yell at my him telling him we needed to pay them hourly to swap the pipes that they installed incorrectly!!! So we not have to pay more to fix the issue that they did wrong. At this point we're almost wondering if they installed the wrong pipes to bill more hours?!?! Most well run businesses will take ownership of their issue and correct it at no cost to the customer (since they are the ones who made the error) but not this company. THE OWNER IS UNPROFESSIONAL AND SHADY INDIVIDUAL WE OR OUR GC HAS EVER WINTNESSED. let me recap...
- wrong size pipes installed but won't take ownership to fix and wants to pay for forchis error
- showed up to the job WITHOUT the tools to complete the job 
- bills hourly for their lunch break 
- sits in their van while still billing you hourly to "trouble shoot" their issue - which is really an easy fix
- also they didn't remove our cast iron pipe which was part of our job bib so GC did it for us... we didn't even make an issue of this but our GC billed us for an hour of labor to do it. 

When I called to speak to the owner he was mysteriously on vacation literally 20 minutes after my husband got off the phone with him on Thursday. I explained to his receptionist to give him a message that I felt homeowners needed to aware of this and I would gladly share my experience if he wasn't willing to make it right. Oh and fast forward a week and half their team did not allow enough room on the pipes for "escutcheons" so we now can't pass inspections! So here it my review. Because he never made the job right. DO NOT HIRE THIS COMPANY. Please save yourself the headache and the frustration of working with this company and find someone else.

I stopped in after receiving a flyer in the mail.  This is a brand new location - and I have heard many mixed reviews (and some bad ones) for Massage Envy - disinterested practitioners, high turnover, etc.

So - with trepidation I booked a $59 Intro Murad Facial with Billie Jo.  She is terrific and thus, I "drank the Kool Aid" and became a Massage Envy Member ($60 per month and you get 1 massage).

I will have my first massage in a few weeks and will update my review at the time.

Front desk staff is very good!
Fantastic. I will keep going until I have worked my way through the menu. You would be wise to seek this place out.

My teen son told me about Circles and Squares great pizza reviews online and social media apps. Found out recently that Pizza Plus in S. Philly has the same recipe/ style of pizzas by Pizza Gutt (Dan Gutter).  Decided to try their plain cheese 9" Detroit style deep dish and  16" handtossed sausage, sauce  and cheese pizza. Both pizzas were very good. Great tasty sauce, yummy quality cheese (not salty like some cheap cheese used at lesser shops)  and the crust was perfect: deep dish was substantial and airy (not  heavy or doughy) and the traditional hand tossed had just thr right "chew" and still crunchy crust. No limpy droop. Stays perpendicular when held with slight fold.  Only wished it was closer to my home. Could be better if they gave it away for free :-)  TWO BIG THUMBS UP

I absolutely loved this spot! It seems to be a little hidden and less well known than other locations, which meant it wasn't crowded. The view was amazing and the water was clear. I really enjoyed visiting and will definitely be going back there!

I can't believe I've never noticed this little ice cream stand.   I bet it's pretty crowded in the summer.    The ice cream is nothing too weird home about, but I bet it's pretty refreshing on an 80-degree day.

You order from a window on the outside of the building and there's some picnic table - type seating with umbrellas.

Pisces has never disappointed me! Their sushi is seriously unique. They offer everything from your basic sushi items to their own chef creations.

The hubs and I went for our anniversary. He got there early, dropped off some goodies for the table and the servers happily met all his requests. Between the employees there and the hubs, the night was perfect!

They even gave us a complimentary glass of champagne. 

I left full and a little tipsy!  We love this restaurant and will definitely be back. 

Oh! And if you check in on Yelp you'll get $5.00 off $30!!! Who doesn't love a coupon!

Do not go here!!!!

The burger was flavorless as well. And the onion rings are gross.

They were also extremely rude to my friend. Took an hour for him to get his food and kept giving excuses. Everyone else sat and ate in front of him and he stayed patient. Only 4 of us were left. Owner was a complete jerk and cursed us all out and was rude when my friend simply commented that the burger took an hour. Beer was wrong for my other friend. Two of us didn't even eat because the manager or owner threw a little baby fit and kicked us all out. We were not rowdy or rude. He simply mentioned that it took a very long time for the food order.

Do you like fresh pasta? Wood-fired pizza? Happy hour deals? Free parking? If so, get on over to Pastaria! They're doing all of the above, and they're doing it really well.

I've been a handful of times, and I'm already settling into my go-to routine. First, I try to go during happy hour to take advantage of their good deals on drinks, pizza, and apps -- hellooo, risotto balls! Weeknights are a safer bet for a shorter wait, but you can always hop on the waitlist via Yelp.

Pizzas range from simple like the margherita to bold like the spicy nduja (tomato, mozzarella, garlic, oregano, honey). Yum! I haven't had a bad pie here.

The pasta is really my jam, though. Go figure at a place named Pastaria! I've been all over the place with my pasta orders, and my advice is to order what sounds good. Whether that's a light sauce, red sauce, short noodle, long noodle, just with your gut, and you'll be in great shape.

And don't forget save room for dessert, or at least a trip over to their gelato counter for some samples or a pint to go.

Some free street parking is available, but I usually take advantage of the free garage below the building. Just a quick elevator ride away from the lobby, this is a great option when it's cold or rainy.

Now that it's getting warmer out, I'm looking forward to enjoying their patio!

Worse PF Chang's I've ever been to! Hostess  had an attitude ; gave us a booth by bathroom and kitchen 
Even though it's late and there were plenty  tables available . Very incompetent waiter . I never complain , but this is so bad and disappointing !
Forgot the name of the po'boy but it was the one with shrimp and fried green tomatoes. It was one of the best I have ever had. The quality was worth the price.

I have lived here since July of 2018. The apartment is very spacious and comes with a storage unit.
The first electric bill was $120 for 10 days but they didn't care. It took a lot of back and forth but eventually they replaced the unit. I noticed that our electric bills decreased significantly after the unit was replaced. I even took it upon myself to contact the previous residents and they told me that they had the same issue and stopped using the AC because they couldn't afford the high bills. I think it's funny that previous residents had this same issue but they kept playing it off like it was nothing. During the first two months we lived here the unit just stopped working on two occasions. After being able to show them how our bill had decreased after the repair they provided us with a credit towards rent.
While others seem to have issues with pest I have never had a pest issue. During my time here I have probably seen one roach (I also live on the 3rd floor). I have, however, had an issue with silverfish. Valet is a pretty convenient option when they want to pick it up. Some days they come as early as 12pm some days they come after 5pm. At one point in time I was served with a violation for having 2 trash bags in my bin (there was no glass or holes. I'm sure they were being petty). However, I have noticed people with multiple bags in their bins who never get served. On another occasion, I was told that I had my bin out too late in the evening. However, I have seen people with their bins out on non service dates. I am finding that I am taking my own trash out more now since the rules are so ridiculous and I can't keep up. The trash pileup on the weekend is extremely unsanitary. I noticed a sign once and that helped the issue. I also noticed that they have placed a dumpster in the middle of the street. I'm not a fan of the dumpster in the street as it seems dangerous and inconvenient. The sign seemed to be very effective so I'm not sure why they removed it. Although there are doggie bags all around the neighborhood there seems to be a lot of dry dog poop lying in the grass. 
The side gate entry box has literally been broken since I've lived here.

I had been inquiring about the process of an addition to my current lease since December of 2020. The assistant (Jackie) and I had a conversation in December that confirmed the individual would need to pay an application fee, go through a background check, credit check and meet the rental income requirements. We also had a conversation on January 7th, 2021 where I expressed to her that my current roommate had left (but her name is obviously still on the lease). On January 12th, 2021 I sent an email about an application for a roommate addition. On January 14th, 2021 I still had not received a response.
When I called on January 14th, 2021 and let her know that I was following up about the email she seemed very irritated. She told me she had nothing to do with it and that it was forwarded to the property manager. I advised her that I was confused because in the email we were simply requesting the application. She continued to reiterate the same thing and made it a point to let me know that the property manager had other task in his queue that are of more importance. I noticed the conversation going left and her anger increasing as I kept telling her I was confused as to what we were waiting on when we just wanted to fill out the application. Eventually, I took the initiative to say "okay, thank you for your time" and disconnected the call.
The next day the property manager (Strato) sent an email letting us know that our request was denied. He mentioned that the way that I spoke to the assistant yesterday was "disrespectful" and attempted to mock me in the email by quoting things that never came out of my mouth such as: "Ok, I don't got time for this"--which I'm assuming is supposed to be his take on "AAVE" and a generalization that he has made on how Black people conduct themselves. 
They replaced my refrigerator three times in 2020. On Friday March 26th, 2021 I noticed a leak. They did not come until March 31st, 2021 to try and resolve the issue although I listed it of high priority. I did not bother following up between that timeframe as I was fearful of once again being painted as an aggressor.
The gym at this property has been closed since March of 2020 (however the pool remains open) but Debbie at The Preserve and Shaneice at Promenade confirmed that their residents at the sister properties have access. I'm convinced they just don't want to give us access at this point. I've inquired about the matter with corporate through mail, email and voicemails since September of 2020 when Florida entered phase 3 but they're an even bigger joke.

You know who I don't like? People who leave one-star reviews. OK, so the waiter forgot your side of basil aioli and the lighting was "meh" and they ran out of your favorite craft microbrew. Get the f**k over it. Did you eat your lamb sliders and actually kind of enjoy them? That's what I thought. Go on and give that gastropub another star or two you jackass. I saw you light up a little bit when you saw they had duck fat fries.

But today, I have to be one of those people, and the reason is Focus Travel.

I've been making random forays into New York since moving to the East Coast over a year ago. I've tried all the "economy" bus lines -- Focus, Cash World Tours, Yo! Bus, Megabus, probably Bolt at some point. They all have one thing in common: they suck. The Yo! Bus was my favorite for a while because it had a nice balance between the bottom-dollar cheapness of Focus and the illusion of luxury that is Megabus, but then it stopped being a thing. On my last trip to NYC I guess I forgot how truly awful Focus is, so I talked my boyfriend into meeting me in Chinatown and hopping onto one of those classically shady, unmarked white buses. The ride would have been fine except for the loud-mouthed, day-drinking South Philly brohams who seemed only capable of talking about titties and Percocet for two hours. (You get some riff raff on a $12 bus ride, go figure.) But overall, it was fine, whatever.

The ride home was another story. First we stopped at the office in NYC to pick up the tickets we bought online (for some reason you have to get a paper ticket even if you pay online, what?) The first person we talked to apparently didn't know English, so we were waved on to to the next window. That person started speaking Chinese to my clearly Caucasian boyfriend, and once he got a good kick out of that, switched to impeccable English. Ha, funny! When we stepped onto the bus I think we both micro-fainted for a second. It smelled like a giant unwashed armpit that had been slathered in barbecue sauce and left to putrefy. The seats were full of trash -- bottles, cans, gum wrappers, dirty napkins, fast food containers. What little trash made it into the actual trash bags wasn't taken out either. I've been on a lot of uncomfortable bus rides, but this was truly revolting. I breathed through my t-shirt until I got used to the smell, and then tried to sleep the rest of the way, making as little contact with anything on the bus as humanly possible. 

At best, Focus Travel is a serviceable, no-frills way of getting from point A to point B. I've had a few rides where I was almost by myself, and the bus was relatively clean, and I guess I was like... sort of satisfied. But more often than not, the bus is just a mess and so are the people on it. In its defense I will also say that it is usually on time (which can't be said for its competitors, ahem MEGABUS) but no matter how cheap your service is, I would expect the bus to at least be sanitary. I don't need wifi or leather seats or a second-run Disney movie, but please at least take out the f***ing trash.

Wasn't bad, wasn't great. It's was a decent poboy with low grade beef in a pre made patty but it was a lot of meat and for the price not bad. Better than New Orleans Hamburger & Poboy but not as good and any of the bars or other poboy places in a few blocks. The artichoke balls were great I must say I enjoyed them.

Service - Good
Taste - ok
Value - fair
Speed - Good

The waiters Deah is an absolutely wonderful lady she's amazing is you go there definitely get her !!!!!  Great personality and great smile and loves laughing. In the matter of me being there for an hour she did great service I loved being there cause of her.

Tria is one of my favorite spots for a low key drink. My favorite thing to do there is get wine and cheese. The waiters are very knowledgeable and will always help you pick out a wine you'll love. I've had quite a few winners here, that I look for when buying bottles now. A great atmosphere and service.

Done with this place.  We have ordered on a weekly basis for years, but we're finally done.  

The delivery driver is bad.  Food always leaking when he gets here, and I know why... we have a 10mph speed limit in the complex and he flies over the speed bumps at 30.

And lately they seem to forget the egg roll we order at least half the time they deliver.  I don't even bother calling them about it.

Between Mario Andretti driving the food here, and the missing egg rolls, we are done with this place.

Stupid to think things would change... Tried to have deliveries from this place again and got wire from what looks like a scouring pad stuck in the dumplings.
Excellent food! Excellent service! Clean facility. Chicken tikka masala was absolutely delicious! Rogan josh was amazing as well. Well worth the price.

The decor is cute and the staff was friendly, but I'm only giving two stars because the air conditioning, or lack thereof, was horrible. I ran the AC all day while I was out but the room DID NOT cool down enough to sleep comfortably at night. I will not be returning to this hotel.

The food is very good and they have lots of gluten free options. I've bee here a few times and it is always pretty good. Had HORRIBLE service tonight though.. Melissa is soooooo slow omg. My life for a water...and I JUST WANT TO PAY MY BILL!

Had a lovely dinner at Contigo last night! 

We began with the Pulpo Galicia (octopus sautéed with lemon, thyme, and capers). It is a generously-sized tapas serving, and we enjoyed sharing it. It was a shade on the salty side, but the octopus was tender and very flavorful. 

Next, we had the Caesar Brussel Sprouts. What an unexpected, delicious surprise of a salad! The brussels are roasted, shaved, and then served as a warm salad in a tangy caesar dressing with pickled onions. Be aware, this salad is quite large -- plan to share it, if you're ordering it along with an entree! We split it between three people and each still had a hearty serving of it. 

I got the Moqueca de Peixe, a seafood stew served over rice. It has a tomato and coconut milk base, with chili oil for just the right amount of heat. I have the impression that it is made with different seafood depending on availability, so the exact ingredients may differ, but mine contained shrimp, mussels, and grouper. It was great! I found myself scraping the dish at the end, trying to get every last bit of the sauce. 

My dinner companions both got the Pescado en Escabeche, which again is made with different fish depending on the night; last night it was a thick, large swordfish steak cooked in garlic, lime, and white wine sauce, served with sautéed squash. Both enjoyed it very much, and had leftovers to take home. 

We finished the meal with the Mexican Chocolate Pot de Crème, a lovely chocolate custard spiced with cinnamon and cayenne. 

This would be a nice spot for a special-occasion dinner, or a good place to bring out-of-town guests. 

Also, while we didn't go for paella, do be aware that if you want the paella, you'll need to order it a day in advance!

Stayed during spring break and found this hotel provides everything we needed. It is nicely appointed to have a reasonably price stayed. The full kitchen is very handy; dish towels, dish soap and dishwasher pods included. Yellow swim towels provided in our room; hair dryer adequate for long hair. Pull out couch fine for children, door between bedroom and living area. Large closet with iron, on-site coin laundry near pool. There are two nice pools, large hot tub and a grilling area. No really onsite restaurant but several dinning choices are within walking distance. The elevator is slow but your on vacation, it's not a big deal. Parking is free and we never had a problem finding a parking spot.

The naan bread was some of the best naan I've had in the States and the tandoori chicken still on the bone we exceptional. The mixed grilled plate was a perfect combination and balance of all three meats, lamb, chicken and beef. Cool atmosphere, we would go back if we ever come back to STL again.

If you're looking for a bike, and these guys sell it, I highly recommend you give them your business.  I bought my first bike from Vince at Triumph Philadelphia and I cannot be happier. For my first bike, I decided to go with a Triumph Street Twin and I'm very satisfied.  No pressure.  Very knowledgeable.  Good deal.  An all around amazing experience.  

I barely ever write reviews but Vince and Triumph Philadelphia exceeded my expectations (which are very high), and I think they will exceed yours too!
This was the worst Subway sandwich I've ever had. It was flimsy, no choices offered! Paid over $20 dollars with all the fees included with Grubhub. I will never order again!

Horrible customer service! I had a made a reservation online, arrived 15 minutes early, checked in and was told to have a seat. Watched multiple people come and be immediately seated. When I approached the desk, and asked about our table was told they were getting it ready. When they finally seated us, I looked around and noticed at least a dozen empty tables. No apology from the girl seating us. The only positive from the evening was our waiter who was very attentive and provided excellent service. Sad that the first impression that guests get are rude, unapologetic, staff.  Will not be returning!
good food, good price, mostly unfriendly and borderline rude employees with staring problems.

Excellent food - atmosphere - staff. When in St. Louis you have to go to The Hill to have Italian food. 

The three of us got something different so we could taste and try. We started with some cheese bread. At first sight it looks like it's going to be bland but that is not the case. They also bring out crusty bread to dip into their oil and vinegar mixture. 

We ordered the cannoli, capellini with butter/garlic and shrimp, and lasagna. All were excellent. My favorite was the capellini as it was light and flavorful. This is our new favorite on The Hill!
Dine in is open again!  The menu expanded and can't wait to try all the other new items!
We called in and they said the kitchen closed at 11. We got there and they told us they closed it 10 minuets ago at 10:20. I don't suggest this place to anyone.

Riding out #Irma at #holidayinnwestshore We booked this hotel as a last resort to escape Miami and were worried that it would be yucky but it accepted our dogs so we booked. I could not be more thankful for this hotel. It's very clean and comfortable! The food is great! The service is excellent! The management and staff have been better then some 5 star hotels we've stayed in! They set up a conference room with games for kids and adults to ride out the storm. They kept us very informed about the hurricane status and kept up the great service throughout the chaos of the coming storm. The general manager Jerry should get an award!! Great Job #greathotel #dogwelcomed #awesomeservice
They changed their fish n chips to cod, but the baked haddock is terrific and large! The pizza sauce has been tweaked to be a bit stronger, and better!

Before you order; Look at how Filthy the place is. Fans on the ceiling, windows, walls, etc. This place is Disgusting. $22- for 2 Gyro lunch plates and 1 drink. My friend immediately said let's leave. I insisted on giving them a try. I can't imagine what the bathrooms look like. I personally don't believe the 5 star ratings on here. I'm sure it's the owners writing those reviews. How has the health department not shut them down?
