Total hell hole.  We have lived here for over 20 years.  When the Wawa initially went in it was a safe place and it was nice to have a place to get gas on this side of Hatfield before the turnpike.  Now I stop there and most times am overwhelmed by the atmosphere.  It's scary. I was cut off by beat up black car, the car full of people beeped at me and eye balled me as I waited for them to move their car. Inside my child was afraid to get a slurpy without me because of grown men who were standing at the machine.  We watched one fill a cup drink the whole thing and throw it away without paying.  What the hell happened to our small safe country town? Thanks Hatfield Township zoning....Thanks Clemens meats.  Looks like it's only going to get worse.  Their ancestors must be rolling in their graves. Sad.

Wonderful little known cafe across from the Capitol Bld on Capitol Street in the ISTA Bld.  Nice selection of breakfast and lunch dishes with a daily special that helps strech your dining dollar. They also have a wide variety of flavored coffees.  Each day has a different selection of soup including a vegitarian offering.  The Chicken Velvet is the same receipe from the Ayres Tea Room.

The staff is friendly and attentive and will soon be calling you by name. So come for the food but eat in for the friends.

Because of their regular stops at the Wash U Med school food truck row, I frequent the fry truck more than I'd like to admit. 

Everyone with a dietary restriction knows the sad drill of going to a restaurant and only being able to order a side of fries. This truck flips that on its head because these are genuinely some of the tastiest fries I've ever had. With options like pulled pork (gf), taco, Greek(veg), and classic fries(ask for no parmesan for veg and no mayo for vegan), you can't go wrong. They are more than willing to accommodate special orders, and my group can eat vegan, vegetarian, gluten- free, and carnivore at the same stop. 

Highly recommend.

I waited for 25 minutes for 2 bagel and I went up and asked about my order that's when they noticed my order is sitting in kitchen. If I didn't ask about my order they wouldn't even care. At the end they got my order wrong!!!!! Only one bagel I got. Such a irresponsible coworkers
My bf and I came on a busy Sunday. The way was a bit long but it was totally worth the wait. My bf's salmon egg Benedict was a bit salty for his taste. Our favorite was the crab meat tots.

Ambiance was good.
Food was 2.5/5.0 the reason was simple. Cauliflower Kungpao was too sweet. Service was too slow.
Over all it is just an ok restaurant and will I go next time ... there are better ones in town.
Great food, beautiful sunsets. Such a perfect addition to the neighborhood. Will definitely be back!

Such a great night !! Bruschetta app was the best I have ever had!!! Margarita brick oven pizza was amazing and so was the margarita drink special. We felt very safe there outside dining , they practice social distancing and all other guidelines.  And the live entertainment tonight added to great night out.  I highly recommend Swarthmore pizza. We will definitely be back.

I love this place to no end. The Cup Cafe is just as fun, quirky, and awesome as the rest of Hotel Congress. The menu is rather small, but still manages to cover the old classics while bringing in some more adventurous dishes. The omelets are fantastic, so are the pancakes, the juevos rancheros, and the side-orders of potatoes. This time, however, I had the cast-iron cooked eggs. It was a delightful egg-dish with a beautiful beschamel - rich with a complex taste and many flavors that my regular-Joe pallete was amazed by. Everyone at my table was interested and dipped a piece of toast for a taste.

Also, and very importantly, The Cup has great Bloody Mary's. My schedule did not permit me to come on Sunday - when the Bloody Mary bar is open, so I just went with a standard. It was great as always. Still, if you can visit on a Sunday, the Bloody Mary bar has every blendable item imaginable that could be put in a Bloody Mary. They have several different types of blends that are great, but the classic always wins in my book. Still, I wouldn't have know that artichokes and blue cheese make sense in a bloody mary were it not for The Cup Cafe. Likewise, its nice to chill in the lobby with friends, sucking down drinks while waiting for your table. It certainly beats sitting on a bench staring at your shoes!

This place is super legit and should not be missed.

Victoria is always attentive and makes sure the accuracy of my order is matched to a tee. Completely satisfied with her service and will continue to visit this location because of her. We need more hard working individuals like Victoria.

An excellent place for special occasions!  The prices are high - but if you consider that a meal typically takes 2 or more hours, a total bill of $100-$130 with drinks is reasonable for a special occasion.

The service if second to none and the ambiance is wonderful!  They are usually booked solid ahead of time on the weekends, so be sure to call ahead!  The staff take the time to thoroughly explain everything to you and offer substitutions if there is an ingredient you are allergic or do not care for! 

They even have awesome non-alcoholic specialty drinks!  I highly recommend the Blackberry Sage Lemonade (all fresh ingredients) and the Virgin Mojito with Passionfruit juice!  

The individual prices can add up quickly... we usually opt for the 4 course Big Night Out Meal with everything included for $90-$120 per couple and have never been disappointed!  Think of the meal as an event and you will have a great night!

They also do specials for holidays like Mother's Day, Father's, Day, New Year's Eve, etc.  

I took my Mother there for the first time for Mother's Day and she said it was her best meal out ever!  I can't wait to take my husband in a few weeks for Father's Day!  Any occasion is a good occasion for the Melting Pot!

Angela and the InnerG Consultant team managed two very important events for me.  The first was my wedding, and it was sublime down to every detail! She heard my hearts desires and brought them to reality in detail! The lighting, the stage setup, the table setup and my wedding started ON TIME! Excellent service and care!

The second was my daughters graduation party. The cut outs of the university, and what Angela did with her senior pics, and various displays academic accomplishments, as well as, photo area were excellent! My daughter was very pleased, and I was as well!

I've been to Zozos a lot in the past. I always love it. What I love about it is the ambiance, which is small quaint Italian feel inside. They have carafe of house wine and the wine glasses are massive, this brings joy into my life. Generally the food is good, but on this day it was not up to par. I could be biased though as recently I had a veal parm from a restaurant which was so delicious I just never wanted it to end. The veal parm at Zozos was not on this level and it made me feel very disappointed. Also we had the mushroom ravioli and also just felt the sauce was lacking a richness of flavor. I will go back as I've had many good meals here, and I hope this was a one off.

I truly can't say enough good things about these guys. Excellent Service!!  They come very quickly,  work fast, are professional and fair.   

What's better, they're honest!!  I had a lock jamming up and was all set to buy a new one, but Shay told me I didn't need a new one, just a clean, and then showed me how to fix it if the same thing happened in the future. 

That's customer Service. 

Thomas - Center City Philadelphia

CLOSED.  The owner can no longer operate any consignment business in Idaho under a settlement reached this week in a lawsuit filed against him by the Idaho Attorney General's office.  If you are one of those who got nipped in dealing with Renaissance, note you have until June 10 to file your complaint with the AG's consumer protection division.

Had I taken the time to write a review three years ago when I did business with the owner, Dale Corson, it would have been an uncharacteristically short one for me of thumbs down.  As evidenced by outcome of the Idaho Attorney General's lawsuit filed against him, it seems I am not the only one to have had problems with his performance.  I'll insert today's news article text at the end of my comments.

I came to do business with Mr. Corson as a result of a referral to him by staff at a high end and well respected furniture store in Boise.  A staff member had been to my home and seeing items I planned to dispose of recommended Renaissance as their 'go to' for customers to consign high end furnishings and shared that his furniture store and perhaps others also used Renaissance to sell some inventory items for them.

I am a 'trust but verify' type so to confirm Renaissance was the right fit I visited the store to see how it was laid out and noted some furniture store labeling on the Renaissance displayed items - although not the store that had referred me - and also higher end brand resales.  I talked to an employee there and I subsequently spoke by phone with Mr. Corson to set up the consignment agreement.  Because I was careful  in coming to choose Renaissance, as the chaos of my experience with this business evolved I was in disbelief for how it differed from the agreement.  Because I was diligent in documentation and follow up, I came out mostly whole at the end of my dealings with Mr. Corson.  But it was only for my diligence and dogged follow up across many months that that was so.  Others seem to have been much worse off and note if you are one you can file with the consumer protection division through June 10.

Here's the article: 

"Idaho Attorney General Lawrence Wasden sued Renaissance Furniture Consign and owner Dale Corson in December. The lawsuit alleged Corson abandoned the store, which was at 1507 W. Main St., as well as two storage units of consigned furniture.  Corson also didn't pay customers for furniture that Renaissance had sold for them on consignment, Wasden said.

Renaissance Consign employees worked for weeks with the store's property management company to return the furniture to its owners," Wasden's office said in a news release Tuesday, announcing a settlement of the lawsuit.

Under the settlement, Corson must pay refunds to consumers and must get rid of the business and its customer and employee records. He cannot operate any other consignment businesses in Idaho. He also must reimburse Wasden's office for its fees and investigative costs.

If he doesn't comply with the settlement, Corson could have to pay a $50,000 civil penalty, the news release said.

Any customers who think they lost money due to Corson's practices should file a complaint with Wasden's consumer protection division by June 10, the news release said.

Read more here: https://www.idahostatesman.com/news/business/article229332274.html#storylink=cpy
Byrsa Bistro is by far the best restaurant here in downtown Kennett! Great atmosphere and amazing food! Highly recommend!

This is a great place to stop for drinks in the French Market. Especially on days when it's hot as hell which describes the weather when I was there recently. I got the Flaming Monkey which tasted strong which is good for the price. It is a little on the expensive side especially when you add a tip and the wait staff isn't the friendliest but that doesn't matter much to me when I'm just grabbing a quick drink on the go.

It's unfortunate how this beautiful atmosphere was destroyed by awful Customer Service. We arrived at 7:30 our food was not even at our table by 8:30!

 We asked for a manager but a waiter( or whoever he was)  kept his personal conversation going for additional 5 mins. No offer from management to rectify the situation or comp the meal. Or even a decent apology! She became defensive and gave excuses for why our food had not arrived. Clearly the waitress had not placed our order in when it was placed. 

I don't care how fresh your food is - paella doesn't take an hour to make!  

As an Ecuadorian - I really was looking forward to enjoying a meal there. What a shame. We will never be going back

When I arrived at this McDonalds at 5:30 am, the menus hadn't been turned on, their was a dirty rag in front of me at the register, and virtually every table was dirty. I mentioned that to the man at the counter--who was having fun-talk with one  of his female co-workers--and he told me that the person who cleans tables will be in shortly. I asked for some napkins so I could wipe my table off. And he's getting paid $13.50 an hour! Shameful!!

I don't know why I keep bothering to come here. (I do, actually..  It's close to my work, and sometimes I just really want Thai food) I remember that Royal Thai used to be really good...  I think maybe an ownership change brought about the "express" and took away the quality.  The food is mediocre.. ok at best, and often just not good..  I'm currently sitting over a way too salty bowl of tom yum soup with 5 sad little rubberized shrimp floating in it..  They might have been cooking for days before I saved them from the pot.  Service is consistently rude/inattentive and the dining room is always filthy/empty.  At this moment, nearly every table needs to be wiped off and the three tables around me need to be cleared.  I am the only customer in the restaurant, so it seems like someone could find the time.

Have only ordered for delivery from the office but have never gotten anything but good food and friendly service.  Only thing i wish they would do is have a website we could go to with a menu and thier daily specials.  Would probably order a lot more if we had that.

Yesterday was my first time trying Byblos and it is one of my new favorite restaurants! The service was top notch, the food was delicious, and drinks were great!

We were warmly greeted by a very friendly waitress who sat us promptly and brought us water and pita bread with an olive oil and sesame seed dip. We ordered Baba ghanuj and falafel as appetizers. My husband loved the baba ghanuj! Very smokey flavor. The Falafal was the best I have ever had and the dipping sauce made it even better. For our entree, we shared the combination kabob platter which comes with shish, kafta, and chicken served with hummus and lettuce, tomato and cucumber salad. I have never had such tender and tasty chicken breast meat. The filet was cooked perfectly. The kafta was great too. The hummus and salad are perfect pairings as the hummus is a great dipper and the plate comes with garlic paste and a Mediterranean flavored dressing as well. The Moscow mule was delicious! My husband had the recommended Lebanese beer. As we were finishing up the waitress brought us two small squares of baklava. One was pistachio and one was honey - they were DELICIOUS. I'm thankful she only brought a small square because I could have eaten a whole plate of the pistachio baklava. It was SO good!

I can't say enough about how wonderful our experience was here from the service to the food. I only wish it were closer to my house. We will definitely return.

Lotus Garden fulfills my wildest 1970's lavish Chinese restaurant fantasies! Walking into Lotus feels like pulling back the curtain of time time in all the very best ways. Though the restaurant has the same decor that it's had for decades, the place is immaculate from the koi pond with waterfall in front to the mirrored ceilings in the main dining room. Who knew that chowing down on Chinese food could (and, honestly, should) be such a gorgeous, sentimental, and intimate experience? 

The menu is huge, but I stick with my tried and true favorites in General Tso's and sesame chicken. Their dinners are massive, so you can count on getting at least two meals out of one. The waiters (dressed up, obviously) will walk you through each course that's included with your meal. Here's what my $11 dinner for one comes with: coffee or tea, crackers and rolls with butter, a massive, gorgeous egg roll with tons of sauces on the side, soup (wonton, egg drop, or hot and sour), pieces of sweet and sour pork, whatever main dish I order, fried or steamed rice, and ice cream. And an added bonus: they bring your main dish out in a large, pretty dish with a silver serving dome lid so you can spoon bits onto your plate with your rice while keeping the rest of your food hot. My favorite part about the chicken is that it's incredibly crunchy and the meat is always good quality chicken breast. 

The waiters are friendly, smiley, and helpful. They swoop in when you need something and make sure to get anything you need. They know their regulars by name and order and make dining there an extra great experience. Need I say more? 

In short, go to Lotus! Live out your 70's Chinese restaurant fantasies! And leave with a full belly and happy heart. See you there!
Nice place.   Service was a but sketchy.   Calamari was great... no greasey.    Crab cake sandwich was very yummy.   We will be back

Beautiful place. Food was just amazing.  I had a BLT which was just as a BLT should be. Wouldn't change a thing. Heirloom tomatoes | double smoked bacon | frisée | basil mayo | sourdough bread. Yummmmm.  
Sirloin Burger was perfectly cooked. Spectacular flavor, juicy, tasty, tender and left us wanting more and more. Will just have to come back. 
Any negatives? Well food was as good as it could be but I found the staff to be a bit dry and unfriendly. They should smile more it would help in making the experience better.

Safelite Norristown sold and installed a rear wiper at the time of my windshield installation. the wiper failed and fell off. Dave O'Donnell with the Norristown Safelite refused to install a new wiper and claims Safelite does not warranty service and installation and the warrant only applies to the value of the part. Dave refuses to discuss and even hung up on me mid conversation. Safelite corporate confirms that Dave is wrong. service and install is fully warranted. If you use Norristown just know that they will not stand behind the Safelite warranty.

Baseball park or Cheesy Carnival? - Either way, it's a bit awkward.

This really doesn't have the feel of a ballpark. It's dark and decorated like a carnival, kind of creepy to be honest!

I have been twice, once while the Rays were in the World Series and this past Wednesday night for a Yankees vs. Rays game. It's a poor representation of our baseball team - they need to build a ballpark for the Rays right next door to our awesome Raymond James Stadium! BTW.. why is it so far away and not in Tampa?

Before I went to sit in my seat I stopped for a beer, paid $9.00. Something I've learned about the Trop.... WAIT to buy your beer until you are in your seat. Apparently, you get bigger beers for $7.00 from the beer people walking the audience. 

I had a hotdog.... of course, I was at a ball game! It was okay, but nothing special.

Nothing  fantastic to report on our outdated ball park , sadly. I felt like I was in a dungeon and was happy to be back in the parking lot after the game. 

It actually makes me sad to write this way about the Trop. I wish I had better things to report. Unfortunately we do not have a choice on where to go see the Rays play... you go to this stadium or you watch them on TV.

If you are going to the game, try to park in another parking lot so you can get out okay, buy your beer from your seat, and buy plenty of beer so you have a really great time regardless of your surroundings.

Cute restaurant,  friendly staff. The cooking area was clean and tidy.  If your menu is simple, make it good...and its good food! As a restaurant owner, I appreciate a well maintained, clean, mom and pop shop. Definitely recommended!

Not worth the money. My co worker said it was the worst Chart House he had experienced. My prime rib came out hot but extremely salty. By the time they brought another dish, my side of creamed apinach was cold. They charged me for it anyway. I finally wound up with the grouper and the sauce tasted like they fortified it with mayonnaise, just horrible. I have eaten all over the world and usually dont post reviews period, but this is the exception!

Absolutely amazing Lebanese food. Best we ever had!  Mazza and homemade pita out of this world! Atmosphere fantastic! Honestly the meal was incredible. We went on Friday night. Friday and Saturday nights the restaurant only offers $60 pp tasting. We did not eat the majority of the entree. For one thing we were already full from apps. But for another we are not big meat eaters. So that part was not worth it for us. Would absolutely go again though. And btw the kannefah was out of this world.

horrible on the hottest day of the year my ac was running great they came for my yearly service check told me i need two switches. $500 later they left. 20 min later my ac is not working so i called.the person i talked to was very rude told me maybe they could be out the next night i told her that was no good i have three fish tanks it gets to hot my fish will die. it was working great before they touched it. she put me on hold for 30 min turns out the tech never hooked up the wires.they are sending out inexperienced techs, going for the money not the service.sad
Gas seems to be a few since higher than Circle K up the street but it's the closest US bank ATM in Westport and the food is better.

has kind of a hippy vibe with random buddhas around the place, but to their credit they have really tasty food. I got the sandwich with avocado and sprouts... simple and clean tasting. A friend got a pizza and was really good without being greasy. definitely recommend if you're around. plus, free parking lot!
Great staff, comfortable place, easy to make reservations and food was very good!  Worth is for special occasions!

I was lucky enough to go to the soft opening and so my review is for today, but I'm sure they will only get better!They had many things dialed in and the place was beautiful.
It's very family friendly with lots of food items, a mocktail menu, and even a area with a big screen tv to entertain the small kiddos while you eat and drink your adult drinks.
The food menu is super solid with wings, pizza, salads, pretzels, poutine, and garlic fries. I really enjoyed all the food I tried. The Pearfection pizza toppings were delicious. My only suggestion would be to make a sturdier crust or lighten the load because I had to eat it with utensils. Not a bad problem to have though! We tried 3 styles of the wings and all enjoyed them, although I prefer "wet" vs dry, but they did provide sauce on the side.
The poutine had moist short rib and a good gravy, just hit me with some more cheese curds. I can never have enough cheese curds! 
As far as the beer, they are serving beers from other local brewers until their beer is ready. I'm told 4-6 weeks. They had beer from Revision, Imbib, Brasserie, and more. I'm looking forward to going back and trying their beer!
Anyways, had a wonderful time in a great space. All the staff we interacted with were super friendly and helpful. We appreciated all of you! Thank you for such a fun day!

Wanted to to try a local business in support of our community.  Very mediocre.  Ordered the pad thai with chicken and got very little chicken and lots of tofu! Ahhh Then ordered duck curry off the menu, which was edible. Then ordered the banana fried dessert which was not edible. Will not return,  sad to say, I  hate to give bad reviews on local businesses.  When I  called to complain...no retribution.

Stopped in for a quick slice around 2:00 the other afternoon and was not impressed. Although I was the only one in the shop, they were upset I inquired about what slice was what. Also when I added a garlic knot it was a real inconvienance to take the two extra steps. I usually appreciate the NY state of mind but this guys attitude sucked.

After the pizza came out of the oven, he put it vertical in a brown paper to go bag so all the toppings fell off. The reassembled slice was tasty but nothing special. What a shame.
Food was good and customer service was great! Definitely a mush visit when in philly.

Well I can truly say I wasn't ready.  The line left me confused and the menu board did not help this 1st timer. But the staff was more than helpful in describing the process. They just couldn't explain the sheer joy you would experience upon tasting this serious delight! All I can say is amazing.  I made my own flavor strawberry and banana...

Went to this place for a surprise dinner date with my husband for our anniversary. It was fully packed because of a thunderstorm and power cut earlier that day and thankfully we had a reservation but they were clearly not prepared for the rush. Our server was also a bartender and made it very clear that he did not have 2 minutes to take our order. My margarita was extremely sour and bitter. I know my cocktails and this was just downright bad. We ordered the free flatbread that we got with the yelp offer and shrimp lettuce wraps. Both were decent. For main course we decided to split a duck that I wanted to be done medium well. Well, the duck comes to our table and it's clearly all pink. The server says he heard medium rare instead of medium well and takes it back. The duck comes back in just 3 minutes with just the outside cooked. It was still pink inside. Our server throughout looked drunk and vanished somewhere during entree and someone else took over. That girl ended up putting the flatbread that came free with the yelp offer on the bill but I'll give it to her that she removed it when we showed her the offer. We ordered a corn bread to go and when we got home and opened the box, we clearly received a half eaten corn bread and we did not have any corn bread left overs from our dinner. This is the service you get when you end up paying $95 for a dinner for two. My suggestion would be to be prepared for the rush. Add more kitchen staff and servers. Your customers don't want servers telling them that "They're working on 10 things at the same time" or "Anything that's not on the dessert tray but on the menu is not available".

Meh, nothing special. I don't see what all the hype was. My hubby & I had the banana splits, 1 traditional & 1 split decision. The bananas on both splits were not ripe in the slightest, they were rock hard & green tasting. The hot fudge was grainy & the strawberry topping tasted more like strawberry jam. The ice cream itself was good but nothing special, probably won't go back.....

I seriously love this place. The beer is on point, the service is very friendly and chill, and the atmosphere is so laid back. Where else can you play life-size Jenga and play video games. Currently my better half is killing some Mario cart and some awesome beer. The food here is great too. I personally recommend the Drunken Fish Spread, the pretzel, and the pizza. It's awesome. Every time I visit my in laws in St. Pete we have to come here!

Reviewing on Memorial weekend, so maybe they were a little overwhelmed.  Decided to eat here from all the positive Yelp reviews, but unfortunately did not live up to the hype. Breakdown:
Pros...great location (can see the fishing boats come in and unload their catch), fish and chips were tasty (very fresh and lightly battered) and clam chowder was ok (doesn't compare to Splash Cafe in Pismo Beach though).
Cons...loud, annoying, drunk people hovering over your table while you are trying to eat on the patio, hot combo appetizer platter was overcooked (mussels were the size of peas) and unflavorful (mussels, clams and shrimp were sitting in a bowl of hot water).
Overall...disappointing.

This is okay to me. I think it's nice to be able to pick your own toppings, but u really don't know what is extra and what's not. The reason is because u see all the toppings, but they are not labeled and u have to ask, what is that and that, etc. By the time, you are finished that surely awesome customized bowl has added up. 

I opted for the Hawaiian bowl. I had add in's and of course it added up to like um, Maybe $16 or 17 I'm pretty sure. That's way too much and guess what, I only had one protein. I wished I could have tried another. I had the marinated tuna.

Happy these places are finally popping up around town. This is probably the closest to me. I hope to find one I can't resist. Till now, it's good to know it's in the area, but I'll keep on finding the one that's good for me.

I will start by saying that this is NOT a place to go to for anything related to Mexican food.  This menu is a very posh, Americanized Martha Stewart version of Mexican food.  That is the negative, and here is the positive.  the decor is excellent, the view outside is excellent, the blood orange margarita is EXCELLENT (sugar rim), and the happy hour is good.  So use this place for a happy hour hangout, not for a real Mexican dinner experience.

If you're buying a 4k TV,  don't you want to see 4k content on it before you buy it?  Don't expect that at Micro Center.  I apparently pissed off 3 employees just by asking the question.  I won't be wasting time in that store anymore. #microcenter #4k

Who voted this burger place number one? I told the young man taking my order I want my burger well done he says "all are burgers are well done" I said "good to know" we go home and my husbands burger is still bleeding if I didn't live 25 minutes away I would have taken it back. And to make it worse all of my sides were wrong. So number one place to eat not..,

Worst customer service experience at a dealership ever. We were in the market for a cheap safe car for a 16 year old about to get her license. My wife and I hadn't planned on buying a car till after the holidays, but I got a message from my TrueCar app about a Ford Taurus they had for 1500. Great deal so we went to take a look. Once we told the salesman which car we wanted to look at, we were tossed around and ignored by the staff like a poisoned hot potato until we eventually left. Both Mico and Damon told us that they didn't have time to help us while they sat doing paperwork. If you don't want to sell a 1500 dollar car then don't advertise one. But don't worry, we won't be bothering them with this or any future purchases.

I've been to Pizzeria Vetri a few times before tonight. The pizzas always have great, fresh flavors, and previously we always had an excellent experience. Unfortunately, today's visit was a let down. 

The service was subpar. Our server was less than attentive. We waited an inordinate amount of time between placing our drinks/apps and ordering main course. I also asked for a menu back to order another drink and it took another 20 min before she came back to take my order. 

The pizzas were tasty, but one was downright cold in the middle. It was disappointing. I think things have gone south as ownership has changed...
Ryan's is your standard college pub. There are two floors, and It's one of the few bars in West Chester where you can play pool.

I was introduced to this place by one of my gf. The best cheesesteak I've ever had, fresh meat, fresh bread, freshhhhhh.   It's a really tiny spot! Lines forms in no time.... BUT they very organized so you get in and get out fast!... I suggest you call in your order, they won't make it till you get there but your order will definitely be placed before the walk ins..

Pro : open full menu on Sunday morning and delivery 

Con :
Pizza is not good . Soggy and raw dough that sticks to wax paper ? Nothing sticks to wax paper, but this did.
Cheesesteak bun wet and soggy also .
Food is fair priced and delivery is fast . Just not I fan of bready crust especially under cooked.
Broccoli bites were good .
J
Pepperoni pizza was excellent and so was the chopped salad.  Service was good.  No complaints.  Would definitely come back.

One of my favorite St. Louis ramen spots and the best customer service. Before visiting, I emailed to get allergen information. I received a reply from Qui himself within minutes. So far, I have tried the Classic Nudo and O'Miso Spicy ramens and I would highly recommend both. Along with the great customer service before coming to the restaurant, the service at the restaurant is top-notch as well. On both of my visits, I have barely sat down at the table before my food is delivered. Truly the best food and the best experience. I can't recommend this restaurant enough and will be back again and again to support this wonderful restaurant and its owner.

Went to Tower Hill to try somewhere new. Figured why not. It was outstanding. Best Tuna I've ever had. Fries were awesome. Lime shrimp was amazing. I can not rave enough about the food. The beers were good too. Very refreshing on the hot day. I would definitely come back.

Currently undergoing a subleasing snafu, will update. Generally pleasant maintenance and staff people. My apartment is poorly heated and sometimes doesn't reach 60 degrees in the winter.

I tried to install my own thermostat, which is not unusual to do in an apartment. They would not provide access to the breaker box which is illegal under the city fire code. They installed it for me and said it belonged to the apartment now. (I also don't have a fire extinguisher.)

They are letter of the law with you but when it comes to compliance to state and local law, not so much.

Good luck if you rent from them. Waiting to see if my deposit comes back.

I have no idea how Brittney L. can comment on someone's "prick"-liness by having a few moments of interaction with the owner. With that said, I found the owner to be quite charming and helpful, in my opinion. But to each her own. 

It's a one stop shop for your DMV needs: license renewal, license plate, transferring of titles and much more. All that with little to no lines! I will definitely be back!
I have been going to the Eye Dr. here for 2 years now.  It's convenient, the staff is friendly, and they do a good job.  I'll definitely be going back.  Thanks Bellevue Eyecare Center!  God bless!

Tried this location after being to the jenkintown one a week earlier. I would say the food was just as good at this one.  Sandwiches and bagels were great again!
The interior of this one is a little nicer but also has very little seating if you want to sit to eat. Only other negative for me about this place is that they don't have any cups for tap(free) water. I don't like buying bottled water, but I might be in the minority. 
I have to agree with some other reviews that the food is not really fast. If you are in a hurry, Dunkin donuts or Starbucks are going to be way faster.

For years I went to another Imaging Center. I found out about this gem of a facility by needing a MRI of the breast, which my current facility did not offer. To my surprise the friendly scheduler called and my appt was scheduled within a couple days at this facility. I was feeling major anxiety since I am claustophobic. From the time I walked in I was greeted by a very lovely staff with a friendly atmosphere. The technician was very kind and thoughtful. He explained every step, played music to my request which helped tremedously and talked me through the exam. My nerves were at ease. A week later I had a MRI on my spine that I was dreading. I would usually request an open MRI but the tech advised the time in the machine I used previously is much shorter. I appreciate that he explained that. My second appt was with a different technician but equally helpful. He gave me headphones for music, eyewear that was soft and soothing so I didnt see the tunnel which helped me greatly and checked in with me during each segment of the test. This is my new "go to" place for future imaging. This is a lengthly review but the facility staff earned 5 stars for being professional, friendly and helpful to calm my fear for a necessary scan. The fact I could feel cool air in the MRI machine was a huge  benefit being a claustophobic person.
 I felt cool, calm and relaxed. Thanks for a great experience. I will recommend facility to others also.

Maybe it was just the night that we went but the only one in our group who enjoyed their meal had gotten a burger, and even he said it was just alright. The wings were awful, and by awful I mean I'd choose the wings at Applebee's over theirs. They were overdone and the chicken was chewy, the breading was falling off and melting into the pile of grease at the bottom, and the sauce had no flavor at all. They forgot to apply the discounts to our bills at the end, and even then the food was way overpriced for what we got. we also watched them chase to guys out of the restaurant accusing them of not paying, turns out they had just left the cash on the table and the waitress had jumped to conclusions. Overall one of the worst dining experiences we've had in a long time.

Steer clear of this company! I took a shot on their 3 month "introductory rate" that wasn't much different than my original electric/gas provider. But on the 4th and 5th month my bile was 2.5x what it normally is. I switched back immediately to my original provider. Save yourself the hassle!
Beautiful salon, upscale. Good workers. Good products. Thank you Elliot for fixing someone else's mistakes!!!!! You did a fabulous job and I will see you in 4 weeks!

Chi is incredible. She is amazing with shape and does quick and beautiful work! Tom is great too! This is my favorite nail place in Santa Bárbara and the only place that never has me doubting how my nails will look when i leave! Lux is amazing :)

All of the food I have had from this establishment is fantastic and made me feel extremely comfortable ordering with their sealed takeout options during the initial peak of COVID. They are a great local business to support and everyone hating on them needs to check and see if their hate is coming from a genuine place of offense or if they are ridiculously nit-picking and looking  for a reason to destroy a perfectly good local business and they are sick for lying about food poisoning.

Best deal on Pass-a-grille beach! The grouper sandwich is huge and delicious, and the 1lb. Order the boiled peel and eat shrimp and split it with someone because it is a generous portion of fresh, tender shrimp that you will struggle to finish by yourself.

On Saturday night, live entertainment fills the space with great music. This place is right on the beach and has outdoor dining, so it isn't fancy. But for a come-as-you-are lunch or dinner spot with great food, this place can't be beat.

Chicken and waffle sandwich.  Chicken breast dipped in sweet waffle batter, deep fried, topped with cheddar cheese and our homemade 4-pepper sausage gravy. Served open faced on a buttermilk biscuit.
I give it 10/10.  Best chicken sandwich I ever had.

My teen son absolutely loved his two slices of pepperoni pizza... aka about half of a large pizza....lol

He said that it was some of the best pepperoni pizza he has had in a long time. He liked that the crust was a bit crispy and soft at the same time. When I asked him to rank it on a scale of 1 to 5, he said a 10!  (I didn't try it, because I have to eat gluten free, which this is not.)

The customer service was top notch! They had genuine smiles, chatted a bit, and the service was really quick.

My son will make sure that I take him here again.   ;)

After I posted my complaint on yelp the store manager called me and got me a tv as good as the original at no extra cost. They did what thy should of done in the first place. In stead it took a month of arguing and frustration and finally a yelp review. Funny. still not to happy with rc Willey oh well.
Terrible customer service. I was there for 20 minutes. Walking around and no one even came over to me. When I ask for someone to help me. The guy looked aggravated. Then I just left.

The hand grenade is bad news. Just a warning. The live music is alright. But this is Bourbon street. If you want good music, find any other street in the FQ.

That said, I can't really say this place is much better or worse than other places on Bourbon St.

The best barber shop in town. I was so happy to find this barber shop a couple of years ago when my son needed a cut. Sir always does a great job. He's great at what he does so you have to make an appt to get in with him. My son enjoys sitting in his chair and listening to Sir and the other barbers joke around. You'll always get a laugh while you're sitting in there. If anyone would ask me where to go for a cut this would be the place I would send them.
Favorite Thai in St. Louis! Service is good and they have a rewards program which is nice for frequent take out :)

OK, so I did not stay for dinner.... so please keep that in mind.
We walked in, no stranger to upscale restaurants, and properly dressed (in sport coats, dresses, etc) and on time....whereupon the hostess promptly sneered at us like we were flies on rats; berated us and then led us past the lively (old men having business dinners with other old men) action at the bar, past the lively action in the front dining room (more farty old farts blabbing) and into an empty space completely devoid of human life, which closely resembled a very fancy closet. 
As soon as we sat down, a waiter immediately arrived, overbrimming with maniac obsequiousness, and proceeding to unspool his crazed stump speech on all of the items on the menu. "No wrong choices, no wrong choices, no wrong choices, no wrong choices, no wrong choices" he repeated over and over and over again as he rattled through the sauces and preparations.
We were all completely freaked out and left at once. 

So, to be very fair and transparent, my one star is for the super evil hostess and the shit vibe. 
Maybe one day I'll somehow end up back here, eat the food and do a 180 (I hear it's very good and evidently Adam West once dined here. Till, then, yikes.... I have nothing good to say.

If you really want to meet mean people, you should visit this UPS Store. I think in their interview process they look for only one quality in their employee i.e rudeness. The owner, the staff everyone is so mean and hostile. I just asked to see if they pasted the return label correctly or not and the lady at the counter got all ballistic on me saying' you should have better pasted it on your own'. Gee if I am paying for the service I sure would want to make sure that things are done properly. 

P.S. Always bring sealed boxes because you will not want to be charged 75cents extra for every box that they seal(this store's policy) and better not ask why they do so because the owner will jump in and get all angry and hostile towards you. Thank you UPS for ruining my day!!!

Well let's say first and foremost the server was Excellent she was friendly humorous and attentive.
The restaurant had a nice atmosphere and was clean.
So why two stars ?2 words.... Quesadilla Burger.just suffice it to say like a supermodel in vogue the menu picture made it look fantastic... However when it arrived it obviously had had a lot of retouching..instead of Cindy Crawford it looked like Broderick Crawford..unappetizing in look and taste.fries were good though.friends had fish n chips said were good next time I'll try that..maybe.

When you just have to have a crepe this is the place to go.  Consistently good and quick. No wifi as the sign says, talk to each other likes its 1995.  Dessert crepes are way too sweet for my tastes but if you're with friends sharing makes it palatable.  Prendre plaiser.
Food is really food! Biggest piece of tilapia I've ever seen. Our waitress is super nice and attentive. It seems as tho she really enjoys being here. Thank you, Sarah.

7th Street is the best of the best.  No other local small business can give you the quality of the big guys with the level of service and care that 7th Street can.  I would highly recommend 7th Street to anybody!!!

This place is so clean, friendly and hospitable!  The food is amazing!  Don't miss this gem of a family restaurant - it's like eating at your Italian Grandma's!  Delizioso!

The fresh homemade bread is delicious!  The fresh pasta makes a huge difference too!  All fresh ingredients and made by hand to order so say you don't want pine nuts in a dish, no problem because it isn't pre-made - whatever you'd like!

Now,I usually don't care for tiramisu, but Fabrizia's is AMAZING!!!  It has almonds and little chocolate bits on top!  The lady finger inside is so well balanced with the custard - incredible!

Call for reservations!  You don't want to miss this place!!

Stopped by here for a break on the way home, this is a very nice open air outlet mall but the store options aren't the best.  Or at least compared to other ones I have been too.  Only plus side is all the food options near by but that is it.

Family owned and run business. Everyone here is so kind makes you feel like family! I love all the food i have got here! Nana makes a killer chocolate cake! They have special dinner nights with mariachis its great! I frequently come here for good food and friendly service! If you havent been you should try it you wint regret it!
Great chicken and great customer service. Would recommend the sandwich and Mac & cheese! Plus, they also have nice outdoor seating that is heated for cold weather.

I was glad to have found this place in the Bywater area. The breakfast options were unique and very tasty. Seating required a short wait, but to-go is certainly a viable option (many folks did that). Upon hearing we were visiting the area, the owner even brought us a small sample of their King Cake. That tells me that they pay attention to their patrons and that's always a good sign to me.

I have a Yellow-naped Amazon and a Yellow-Crowned Amazon parrot. The Yellow-naped Amazon developed a serious upper respiratory infection that was successfully diagnosed from cultures and treated at the Avian & Exotic Animal Clinic. Dr. Lennox frequently treats birds. It is important to take birds to an avian veterinarian, because birds problems are very different from those of dogs and cats. I have a friend who lost a parrot, because a dog-and-cat vet tried to draw blood and did it incorrectly.
The drinks are fantastic and the atmosphere is very peaceful and relaxing. The staff are great and have really interesting taste in decor. Great experience all around. Fully recommend!

My husband and I ate here today and thought the food was fantastic. Especially the macho burrito. I'm giving Chuy's a 4-star instead of a 5-star because we stood at the front counter for a good five minutes and were noticed and ignored by several members of the wait staff before the hostess came out and seated us.

From the same folks from Noble Rice, Noble Market sells specialty Japanese foods. They have a variety of oriental dry goods, like seasonings, various instant ramen, and Japanese snacks.  They also have lots of chilled drinks on hand, like coffees, Calpico and aloe drinks. 
 Since they are newly opened, their shelves have some empty space, but there are promising selections of sake coming.  In the fridges, they also sell packaged sandwiches, ready to take poke bowls and bento boxes.  They also sell specialty meats by the pound, like pork belly, chirasu pork and wagyu beef.  Like any specialty store, the prices are a bit steeper than the local oriental mart, but Noble Market is your one-stop shop for fine Japanese goods.
Food poisoning yesterday from eating there the night before. Not much else I can say about that except the obvious - not recommended.

Food: Limited vegan selections aside from pita and hummus, nachos with salsa/guac, and salads. However, the kitchen staff will work with your server to put something together, so just ask! No, the veggie wrap is NOT vegan even if you ditch the cheese!! Same story with the portobello burger, unless you also ditch the bun! I get appetizers and sides when I visit. Since I love fresh veggies & hummus, I just get it with a lot of veggies and no pita. Their beer menu is great and the cocktails are delicious. 

Service: Friendly, attentive, and holy heck: the kitchen staff must be in some kind of competition to have the lowest ticket times. Everything arrives super quickly. (Which is good; after shopping one can get hangry.)

Ambiance: Nice, dark bar. Good selection of hits from the 90s/00s/today. Lots of TVs for any game you'd want to see, and a projector for the big ones.

Overall, Bar Louie is great place to hang out on a Friday or Saturday evening, or just drop in on a random weekday. The only thing that would make Bar Louie better is if they added some more veganizable vegetarian food to the menu.

A couple of friends and I were able to snag a last minute reservation that opened up tonight, and we were all so happy we did. Possibly one of the best meals I've ever eaten in NOLA in the 12 years I've lived here.

The restaurant itself is lovely - decorations are minimal, but beautiful. The seating was comfortable, the staff was wonderful, our waiter was very friendly & informative, and we were checked on by the chef & the manger of the restaurant (the family who owns/runs the restaurant) - both were so very gracious & warm & welcoming.

The food was stellar. We started with the Bombay Shrimp, the Pakoda, and the Crabmeat Pudha. Each dish was as delicious as the next. The shrimp and cauliflower were especially out of this world. 

For dinner we ordered the pork vindaloo, the goat masala, and the chicken briyani - all of us sharing bites from each other's plates. While each dish was delicious, the chicken briyani was outrageously good. It was served in a mini iron dutch oven, it was a huge serving (even with all three of us eating generous portions from it - I still had some leftover that I was able to take home (their to-go bags are fabulous, by the way!)), and the further down into the mini dutch oven you went, the more flavorful & delicious it was. We also tried the garlic naan and the truffle oil naan. Impossible to decide which was better. Both were so so SO good. We told our waiter to go ahead & select the roti sathi (or bread companions) for us - and he brought us royal paneer, gobi & daal - which were all terrific! 

We also shared two desserts - the jammin' jamun, and the flan me to the moon. The fig-date-praline ice cream is quite possibly the most delicious ice cream I've ever had. And while I'm not normally a fan of flan, this flan was firm & creamy.

It was a fabulous meal, with fabulous service.

I live in Nashville, so I haven't actually stayed at the hotel.. BUT the restaurant/bar on the 4th floor is a hidden gem!! My friend heard about it through the grapevine, and we went for happy hour one day. We have now been back several times!! They do $5 apps and $7 cocktails... both are SO good and can be filling if you grab several to share with friends!! I love this spot, and it never has a wait or is overcrowded because it's so lowkey. We've always had the best service here too!

Kept hearing about the wings. Get the wings get the wings blah blah blah. So finally I caved. The Eagles were beating the Patriots the other night and I felt festive so I ordered takeout. got the "I dare you" flavor, expecting the basic "we pretend these are spicy" traditional wings to satisfy my craving. My girl got a black bean burger and really good fries with cilantro I believe. The fries and burger were good but the WINGS. OH WOW! Spiciest wings I have ever had in my entire life. I loved them. They were insanely hot. Finally a place owns the spice level that they designate their wings. I will be returning for them. Thx landmark!

The takeout traveled well.

I REALLY like this place. I will be back. Let me preface by saying their food/drinks are a bit expensive...even for the thought/dedication that goes into the drinks. $12/drink for most drinks. Apps range from $6-$15. I had the oysters. There were 5 of them. They were very good...but $15 is a lot of money. But lets focus on the positive. You're basically walking into a pre-prohibition bar. The ambience is amazing. The bartenders look...handsome and well-trimmed. They are really good what they do. They will make you drinks that aren't on the menu if you just let them know what your taste is. Be careful, you might get lost and miss this place if you don't know exactly where it is. It's discreet. But it's an experience that you've likely never had.

This place is amazing!  It is nestled along side the railroad tracks which must of been an old wherehouse.  The have done a wonderful job converting it into into a local brewery.  The beer beer and beer and food were great.  We revived great service and we're given and mini tour of the operation.  Very passionate about what they do and it shows. Steve Is wonderful.
A great, low-key neighborhood establishment. Good craft beer and bar bites at an affordable price.
This is one of the best Chinese food I ate in a long time. Great atmosphere and the decoration is beautiful. Come check it out!

Oh yelp, you've steered me awry this time. When I went to El Rey, yelp had given this place 4.5 stars.  I was blown away by the stars, but not by the food.

The food isn't bad. The chips as a starter was actually really good. Tastes fresh, yet not oily at all. And when dipped into the green sauce on the table, it had the perfect amount of crunch and spice.

The rest of the food was just average. The menu was all over the place - I was looking for a Tinga burrito - not offered. However, there's Tinga fries! Wifey wanted a shrimp taco - not on the menu. But they did have shrimp fajitas! The waiter said the chef would be able to make it, but it's weird that it's not on the menu. So wife did the shrimp fajitas.

The fajitas came out quick, but came out incorrect. Wife requested her entree have the salad's sour cream on the side. They brought it out with sour cream on top, and an additional side of sour cream. No big deal, but later I was charged for the additional side. And they took her plate back to just take off the pieces of lettuce with sour cream. And yes, I said plate. Aren't fajitas usually served on skillets? Not here. Came out on a plate, already cooked. She noted her shrimp was grilled very well, but there wasn't too many pieces of shrimp. Lots of onions though.

My carnitas burrito came out ginormous, but it seemed short on carnitas too. And there's no sour cream on the burrito - I used my paid-for sour cream for that.  I only ate half as I was full from the chips. No sauce on top of your burrito either as some other places do with mole, tomatillo, or verde.  Not offered here.

Service was really friendly, and the place isn't too big (in a somewhat busy plaza), but I think the food leaves a lil more to be desired than I'd like.  And the prices aren't THAT great. Because of that, I probably wouldn't try this place again. Too many places in the area that offer Mexican, so onto the next one!!

Hum this to the tune of Lady Gaga's "Bad Romance"

Oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh-oh! I'm going to split my pants!

That's what I was singing after I tried to eat a complete Luke burger.  Oh my Gaga, that thing was a monster!   Did I eat the whole thing?  You'll have to read on to find out.

Was staying at the Hilton and several people recommended eating at Luke and we're glad we did.   We each had a great tap beer...b/f had the jaeger schnitzel, bffc had the flamenküche which is like a pizza with Alsacien onion, bacon, 
caraway and Emmenthaler cheese.  That was off the charts delicious.   

I had the burger which was just so delicious but it was huge!  As Richard Gere said in "Officer and a Gentleman"...No, sir. You can kick me outta here, but I ain't quitting.  That's what I said when the giant burger was set before me (ironically, there was no MAYO-nnaise on it).  Anyway, I couldn't finish it.  I had to quit.  Guess I was more like David Keith's character than Richard Gere's!  (Read the synopsis on IMDB to see what happened to him if you haven't seen the film)

Our server was delightful...she had great suggestions, a lot of enthusiasm and clearly loved her job.  This Besh guy, the celebrity chef of Luke, really knows what he's doing.  I'm a fan.

This food lifted me up where I belong.

I've been to Detour three times now for trivia with friends, and it's... just fine. The first time, I made the mistake of ordering Chicken Piccata, which was a special. This is not the kind of place you order a dish like Chicken Piccata. You order bar food here, and the bar food is pretty good! My fiance understands this and he always orders the wings, which I've tasted and they're quite good. I've also had their steak fries and they're very good! But everything here is more expensive than it should be. Wednesdays, they have half-price bottles of wine, and I got a good bottle last time. But the kicker for me and the reason for the three-star review, is the unattentive and, honestly, evasive service. I get that the servers are busy, but good luck if you, say, didn't get silverware before they dropped off your meal. I approached the server station, where two servers were printing receipts and doing other work, but neither of them even acknowledged me standing there. I had to find someone else to ask for the silverware. We'll keep coming for trivia because our friends like it, but I wouldn't come back if it were up to me.

I, like other Yelpers, was surprised at how expensive the produce was at this Giant. $2 for a single avocado seems quite astronomical. The merchandise for sale is varied, though, so if you're looking for your favorite brand of pita chips, you're likely to find it. This Giant also has a weird, low roof, which just makes the location seem very cramped. Additionally, its parking lot is a little cramped and twisty, and can be hard to navigate on foot because cars whip around corners willy nilly.

However, the cashier was very pleasant and the Giant has a killer location, with lots of other useful stores located next to or near it.

Natures Food Patch Market and Café is one of the best natural food markets in the area. You will find a large assortment of organic fresh fruits, vegetables, meats and fish. Also a large assortment of hard to find natural, organic, non-GMO products. The aroma when you first walk in the door takes your senses on a health trip! I would highly recommend this business to my friends and associates.
Admittedly, I've only had burgers & salads here, but they're REALLY good! Sandwiches are HUGE, service is slow but friendly, not a place to go if you're in a hurry, but worth the wait if you're not!

Time and time and time again VGP makes sure to stir up what seems to sometimes remain a stale music scene in the Philadelphia area. Over the past year and a half I have been consistently blown away by, not only the diversity of the music acts they bring to the stage, but the diversity of different venues and clubs they bring these acts to. 
What really pushed me to write my first Yelp review on VGP was the recent announcement  of the Benefit For Environmental Justice in Equador taking place at The M Room on October 23. When I first heard the name of Joe and Alex's production company of course I thought of The Kink's. But what I also thought about was the idea of being green and using their name in to contrast benefits like the upcoming one at The M Room.
I always lok forward to VGP's upcoming announcements and shall stay friends with the VGP crew forever and ever. Thanks!

The atmosphere at this place was awesome. The greeter was warm and funny. The people that worked there actually seemed happy to work there. We ordered the spinach dip along with the catfish platter and shrimp po-boy. Everything was great and savory. I would definitely go back on my next trip to New Orleans. A calm place in the mist of the storm of people on Bourbon street.

If I could give 0 stars I would. I came for Mardi Gras and booked a walking tour with you guys for 4 people. We came and soon realized we were part of a group of over 35 people and me being hard of hearing could not hear anything the guide was saying because there were so many people. Many of the people who were there did not have tickets to go on the tour and our "guide" never even checked to see if we had paid. We had to leave bc this tour is not ada compliment in any way nor was I just going to wander around with this huge group and not be able to see or hear anything. I emailed the company and instead of refunding me, they said we could go on any of their tours for free, well that's not helpful seeing that I live in Seattle and they only have them in Charleston, Savannah, and Nola. Honestly I'm really disappointed and now out over $50 for something that I couldn't even participate in.
Granted I'm not a huge ramen fan, but this was the best I've ever had.  Spicy ramen with pork shoulder was excellent!

I am very satisfied with my French manicure by Jessica...she did a great job! I only stopped in because my regular nail lady is on vacation & now I have two that I love !!! If you go to iNails ask for Jessica you won't be disappointed!
DO NOT STAT HERE! Loud guest shouting all night and the staff is rude and does not care

We're dating back a few years now, but La Peg had delicious food for restaurant week. It was (obviously) reasonably priced, well-cooked, and with enough options to please everyone involved. The atmosphere is really unique and industrial while still allow for some relaxed and romantic energy to encircle the room. The waitstaff was friendly and helpful while our indecisive party figured out what to get. I would definitely go back even without the discount.
The rack of lamb will have you come back for more. It's a nice place to go after a open house for your son's school (Haverford Boys School)
Lots of healthy great choices. Very accommodating and friendly. Prices are fair and food is fresh and delicious.

We just moved from the Seattle area (Bellevue) and the Total Wine stores there have much larger stores and a much larger selection of beer and wine.  We end up going to Plaza Spirits & Beer because at least they have a better selection even if it is more expensive than Total Wine.  We asked our cashier why the puny selection of beers and she said it was the fault of the distributors and that other customers had asked for more/different beers to no avail.  It seems if Plaza can get a large variety of beers then whey can't Total Wine?
Also we have found when we visit the store it is frequently torn up with ladders everywhere and the shelves virtually empty.  Not sure why but it is discouraging to us since it makes it VERY difficult to shop.  Can't this type of work be done at night?  The managers and employees aren't exactly friendly or helpful; actually they look miserable.  Once we were lucky enough to snag an employee who helped direct me to the beer I was seeking but usually they are chatting amongst themselves or with the vendors.  We are hoping over time the beer assortment will improve.
This place was awesome. The staff was friendly. The eatery was clean. I got the lamb kabob. It was tasty and fresh. I will definitely go back
Love coming here for brunch on Sundays! Had Julia as a server the other day and she was wonderful! Keeps the drinks full and makes sure the food comes out quickly.

Great spot for breakfast.  Service was exceptional.  Austin our Waiter had great recommendations and all of our orders were cooked to perfection!  Sweet potato pancakes were awesome. Highly recommend.
This place never disappoints! The nachos with chili were enough for 4 people and hands down the best in downtown Tampa. The Philly cheesesteak is amazing as well.
excellent wings, po boy was very good and service was excellent

Very personable and fun.  We had a beautiful and smooth flight around Santa Barbara and the sights.  Highly recommended.  Dan was very informative and friendly.  His tours would be an excellant addition to any event or corporate function.  Or if you are about to propose, he has some excellant suggestions for incorporating that into a romantic flight!  Do it!  You will love the experience!

In an unassuming strip mall in Franklin, this place looks like everything else in Franklin. But inside is a clean, wonderful place with yummy vegetarian food. When we visited, 75% + of the clientele were Indian. Good sign! I love Indian, and vegetarian buffets mean I can eat everything without fear of meat or meat products being in it, which is rare! They bring fresh, buttery naan and dosas to the tables. The weekday buffet was $10.95, a steal! I tried several things, but especially liked the samosas, the paneer tikka masala, the hakka noodles, and the kheer. The carrot dessert was also unique and yummy. Some of the items a little spicier than on more Americanized buffets but it was fine for me, and I'm one to stick to mild. The service was excellent and our waters were kept filled. Overall excellent experience.

Stopped by the other day and browsed around while waiting for our sandwiches. It's a little pricey ($5.99 for sriracha?) but the selection of food is well-curated and appealing (I am a huge nerd and little yellow tins of mustard powder make my heart sing). 

The sandwiches were tasty, at $6, I got a generous portion of basil chicken salad (though I feel that the sandwich could have used something more--lettuce, tomato, onion? Anything), and my boyfriend liked his pressed caprese panini. I LOVE Joe's Iced Tea, so that was a welcome accompaniment. We had originally planned to get the sandwiches to go, but were convinced to stay so that we could split two scoops of Basset's coffee fudge ripple ice cream (it had little coffee liqueur-filled candies mixed in, come on!) on the way out.

All in all, not exactly easy on the wallet, but very cute, pleasant, and tasty.

Have tried this place 3-4 times, have never left satisfied or thought they had good service. They are good for watching sporting events, have a lot of TVs and a lovely outside patio. They need to amp up their service game and menu. Menu is very limited and the food is okay but nothing special, bar food. Was disappointed once when we came during "brunch hours" (very few things on brunch menu) and weren't able to order any lunch items. Last time we went for a friend's birthday, had a party of 10. There was one server, her first night, working the whole upstairs with multiple parties. Horrible organization. She forgot multiple drinks and orders and completely messed up the checks at the end. This was no fault of her own, but the manager that stuck her with all these tables on her first night, a Saturday! The ambience is there but that's it.

Love Pho and it was the first time at this place.. pho Nola is good and good taste.. Vietnamese Spring roll is fresh and good too.. Last time I visited LA, I had Pho at Fusion Cafe which I felt big disappoint.. But this place is much much better than Fusion.. Only my suggestion to Pho Nola is to have a better Service with smiling from servers which makes customers feel good.. Other than that food is good..

Tucsonans!  (Tucsonites? Not sure what we call ourselves, honestly.)  We have a West African restaurant in town!  We really deserve all those foodie accolades.  I've had two stellar visits to Alafia.  A few highlights: the chicken in red sauce; the fried fish; the hibiscus juice ('bissap'); the ginger juice (the most authentically gingery concoction I have ever tasted); and--for those who can take heat--the homemade hot sauce, which is so fantastic that we now buy it in bulk. 

According to the ex-W. African Peace Corps volunteer in our group, the meal, the menu, and the atmosphere are all authentic, so there's the added benefit of getting the real thing.

This establishment seems to have gone somewhat downhill in 2019.  Before 2019, it was fantastic but the last time I went (late 2019) it didn't meet expectations.  Service was a little off.  Our table's totem pole thing was green and they still passed us.  The quality of food didn't seem like it used to be, but it was still okay, so I am a little bit worried.

I've been to a different location before for coffee and it was delicious, but I wanted to try the food. I got a grilled cheese sandwich. It was Brie, cheddar, and a seasonal fruit compote (which was a delicious add). The bread was good, but weird to have it crust free - felt childish - and I like crust!! But it was delicious. I also got a cappuccino with oat milk. It wasn't the best cappuccino I've ever had, but it hit the spot. They have oat milk and almond milk, which is fantastic. This location is so beautiful with the huge windows and all the plants. The staff was friendly and at the end when I wasn't sure where I was supposed to bring my dish (it's on the other side of the counter if you head towards the Poydras tower entrance) they pointed and then on my way towards it they just said they could grab it from me. It was a small gesture, but appreciated. It was a nice quiet place to enjoy my lunch and read my book.

Worst place to shop!   I've never been insulted in my life!!! Prejudice as can be.  I have never been at any store and have been asked to leave my purse outside the dressing room!!! Mind you my purse was no bigger than a 6 inches in size.... Not to mention I am the only one that left my purse...  I don't know about any of you, but purse is somewhat personal just to be left blatantly without anyone watching it.  I truly felt because my color ain't right they thought that I would steal... Hell the place was so unorganized anyways.

Please the store was in such disarray that you can't find anything at all... Needless to say, I am so disappointed

You'd think people had never eaten a hamburger before.

When I hit Hi-Pointe Drive-In the other day, there was a line that probably would have extended out the door, except it was kinda cold out, so instead it snaked around the inside of the restaurant, clogging the aisles in the dining area.

If there had been a fire, I probably would have made it out alive, but let's just say it wouldn't have been pretty.

The night before, someone had smashed one of the glass doors with a brick, maybe to protest Der Fuhrer, or maybe just because they wanted a hamburger and they didn't want to wait until the following morning.

Outside, there was a guy either filming a segment for the local evening news or surveying the landscape for a forthcoming construction project. I don't know enough about the equipment they use to be able to tell.

I figured I might be in line for a while, as if this were Thunder River, and I was concerned, because waiting for food makes me emotional, but I was out of there with my to-go order in about 20 minutes.

When I saw the line moving so quickly, I figured this might be a matter of them having come up with some high tech way to put together hamburgers, but come to find out they're using a system not unlike the one at one of my first fast food jobs, at Hardee's.

It seemed as if all of the various parts of the burger, including the meat, had already been prepared, and when you ordered all they did was pile them on a bun, set it on a tray and hand it to you. The whole process couldn't have taken any more than like 90 seconds.

I don't know that my burger was significantly worse for not having been slaughtered and butchered out back in the parking lot of the movie theater while I waited, but it just didn't seem right to spend $10-plus (for a burger and fries), i.e. my weekly dinner budget, for something so easy to put together.

I had the Smash 'N Grab, the daily special named for the incident the night before. It consisted of a burger with caramelized onions, bacon and brick cheese, whatever that is. I was already gonna get a bacon cheeseburger, so this was--as Dewey Oxburger might put--perfect for me.

The caramelized onions were reminiscent of the rehydrated onions (rumored to be cabbage) at White Castle to an extent I wasn't prepared for. The brick cheese had congealed a bit by the time I got it home, and that may have actually made it better.

The meat was a bit more done than I require. (Ahem.) If I'd been thinking, I would have tried to get it mid-rare. Maybe they would have been forced to make it fresh.

The fries were natural-cut, which isn't necessarily my thing. Savage that I am, I prefer the thoroughly processed fries at fast food restaurants, but these were pretty good for what they were.

I'd definitely come back, but probably not until either the hype dies down some or they open another location.

Pluses about this hotel:

Flat screen tv

Nice clean good size bathroom

Neutrogena bath products 

King size bed comfortable

Small microwave & fridge 

Lap table

Nice breakfast area - free breakfast. 

Restaurants & stores close by

Free wifi

Reasonable rates

Military discount 
honored

Will use this hotel again when visiting NOLA.
Rayna is excellent! She's personable and so great at what she does! She's been cutting my husbands and I's hair for years and never disappoints!

Came here on a Tuesday night with my cousin and her dog. They are very dog-friendly, so your pouch will be given a water bowl and snacks if your request. 

Situated along the river walk, the location of the restaurant is nice, though in the evening it can get chilly and a little windy, so bring a jacket if you plan to eat outdoors. 

Overall, the food was good. If you're dining out with 2 - 4 people, you may want to consider ordering several of their delicious appetizers and sharing. We ordered the mussels, the bruschetta, and the pita and hummus, which was just the right amount of food for two people. 

Our server was very friendly, and the prices here are reasonable. Nice ambiance, and the live musician (acoustic guitar) was super good!
This is a go to spot for my friends and I. My favorite wings in Tampa and fantastic pizza as well. We go once a week and enjoy a beer and food out in their patio.

I've been here two times. They have the latest hours of any place I know which is great for me because I work late hours and when I get off everywhere else is closing. They do nice work and have a big place so there isn't too much of a wait.

My mom came in to visit and had this place in mind for dinner. We arrived around 6 and were told we'd have a 10 minute max wait, which turned out to be a 25 minute wait in the end. The service was slow, but the menu was big. We ordered mushrooms for the table. The taste was good, but the texture was rubbery. Overall the food was fine but paired with the wait, the slow service and the sub-par atmosphere, it wasn't a place that left an overly positive impression on me.

Today I had some of the best lasagna ever made.  It was a surprise.  I had not eaten at Oakley's since it came under new management.  I walked in at 2pm and saw they had Sunday lasagna. I love lasagna.  So I ordered some.  I got the last piece.  The owner told me that people line up to get the lasagna and take it home for the family meal. I understand why.  I was so blessed to get that last piece.  It is made with fresh pasta and mozzarella.  The sauce is house made.  It is unbelievably creamy and smooth.  It is a huge piece so I took half home and if I'm feeling generous, I will share with the rest of my family.  I will return.  Next time, if I'm not still dreaming of the lasagna, I will order his pasta with smoked salmon in a cream sauce.  And I will need to keep coming back to try his other amazing Italian dishes.  I understand the burgers are good too!  Looks like there's lots of good eating in my future!

Well we ate at this location a few years back and wasn't pleased - figured we'd give it another try since it had been awhile. The service here is what keeps us away. We pre ordered and although the food was ready to go we ordered drinks when we got there so the shakes wouldn't be runny on the hot day. As soon as we got the food I ordered soft drinks to have with our meals and ordered shakes as well. She went inside and didn't come back out, expected to pay and have the soft drinks given to us to have with our food - but instead I sat waiting at the door to pay while she made the milkshakes. 10 mins later my family is done eating and no longer even needs the soft drinks we ordered and ended up having to wait for me to eat therefore eliminating the purpose of pre ordering the food. Anyone in the food service industry should know drinks come out with the food, specialty items can be delivered afterwards - she didn't even seem to care about the clearly mistaken judgment - no apology and just seemed irritated by my request to no longer serve us the soft drinks we didn't need anymore. It's too bad but save yourself the disappointment and go right up the road to Main Street Burger - consistent food and family style service.
I am a member of their wine club and was finally able to visit their tasting room in Santa Barbara.  We had a great time and tasted delicious wine! Can't wait to go back!

I wish this restaurant was in my area. It was an amazing experience! It brought back memories of my trip to Argentina... Fabulous food, wonderful people! Hoping to get back to Philadelphia and experience this again!
Honestly a 10/10 the shrimp and pastor was amazing and we tried this new almond salsa that was bussin. Highly recommend if you want quality tacos. Also a lot of coffee options around it! (:

Casa Molina is an absolute classic, and this location in particular is my favorite. What puzzles me is that I have not yet composed a review for the place, so now I am.

To start, I have been here countless times--probably 20+--and have always enjoyed the food. I have had everything from their enchiladas de la casa, to their chicken mole, and even their combo platters and caldo de queso. I have yet to have anything on their menu that turned out to be a swing and a moss on their part, and their caldo de queso is among the best I've had. The overall vibe I get from the food is very home-like.

Now onto that dining room, which is probably one of the coolest ones I've ever seen in a Mexican restaurant. The beams, tile, and lighting make for a very nice place to be on evenings out.

Wait staff is always welcoming cordial, and they give you lots of time to look over the expansive menu. They are also very fast which is good as this place can really get packed at dinner time.

The only negative thing I can really say is that the prices, as others have mentioned, are a bit on the pricey side. Now, while the food is delicious, there isn't anything particularly fancy going on here with the ingredients, preparation, or presentation; it's honest, home-style Mexican fare, which I like. I feel they should probably charge accordingly. I see Italian places suffering from the same problem from time to time.

Well, that's a wrap and I am officially getting anxious for another trip back because I need some more of their caldo de queso in my life.

I tried to order four items from the menu and they didn't have one of the major ingredients for each plate. They interrupted the cashier while talking my order.  Then I received my soups cold and the plate was messy. The person that serve the food was rude! You can notice the lack of training in customer service. Now I understand why the mall has so many options for dining!
Fucking ridiculous, I hate that I'm wasting more of my time. Service sucks. Manager ate while we waited for our food for over an hr. Our friends had to leave before they got there food. I'm done.
