It's hard not to love Publix in general, but this is easily the nicest Publix around. They have a sit-down deli, an amazing arrangement of fresh sushi, and their ethnic food section is huge!! Not to mention they have a parking garage for when the weather is less than desirable. 

I walked in today and every staff member smiled and said "hello" as they walked past or stocked the aisles. The sushi chef asked if I needed anything made to order. It was like walking into grocery heaven. 

If you don't thoroughly enjoy your shopping experience at this Publix, then you're just crazy.

Fuji Sushi is a favorite for my family and I! We get takeout at least 2-3 times a month from here. Everything we order is consistently fresh and delicious. We have never been disappointed with our meal. 

Some of our favorite menu items are the chicken and shrimp fried rice, the hibachi dinners, the Fuji I, II, and III rolls, Hawaiian roll, Bree's roll, po boy roll, the list goes on! Literally ever single special roll that we have tried was on point! They are open to creating any custom roll that you request which is perfect when you have picky children. ;) 

When we want to keep it simple, we order the crunchy roll, California roll and the spicy tuna roll. Everything is always fresh. I have had tuna rolls at many sushi joints and let me tell you, Fuji has definitely been the freshest!  

Another favorite is the seaweed salad! Always fresh and good! 

Another great thing about Fuji is that they are genuinely kind and every time we call or go in they go above and beyond to ensure we have the best dining experience and leave happy. 

Overall Fuji Sushi is EXCELLENT! Definitely deserves 5 stars,  if not more.  It's a hidden gem for sure and I would recommend this place to anyone who is looking for quality, fresh, affordable sushi.

Stopped in solo for a quick snack. Had a pickled plum roll. It was good, but there could have been more pickled plum in it and less cucumber. I asked for spicy sauce on the side and was given a generous amount with no extra charge which I appreciate greatly.

The restaurant is small, intimate, quiet, clean and cozy-feeling, although I was privy to my neighbors' conversation a bit too much due to the close proximity, I think it was because it was midday and there were only the two of us in there. The service was fast, attentive and polite. I would come back again from the look of all the yummy maki, if I knew they did veggie-substitutions, since there were only a handful of veggie rolls on the menu, but I was too daydreamy to ask that day. 

Overall, a positive experience! I give kudos. :)

Popping brunch spot on a Saturday or Sunday afternoon. This was my second time here and it's just as fun as I remember it the first time. The DJ inside the place makes it so lively. Feel like I'm at a party in the morning.
This time I got the egg and brisket bagel sandwich and it was delicious. They added a garlicky cream on the side that made it so delicious and the brisket was the perfect Smokey flavor (this coming from at homegrown Texas gal). 
Definitely recommend reservations if you want a time slot before 1pm. The reservations booked out by like wednesday or Thursday the week I went. 
Will definitely come back for more and to hopefully try the delicious breakfast sweets next time!

Great food. Had the combo plate with steak and chicken, rice, pitas and Greek salad. $15. Delicious, great spices and flavor and large portions.

I also tasted the Greek feta burger and fries. Yummy and only $10.

Nice friendly service and they gave us a free pita and hummus platter when we sat down.

Easy to find and plenty of free parking.

I was going to the Mexican store right next door and I decided to pop in to attempt to get a bagel for my fiance. Sadly they were out of any sweet pickles I didn't think to get him a regular bagel with cream cheese. I said got him a couple of Boston Donuts which he thought were good and I ended up picking up a cronut for myself. I only ate half a cronut as I'm trying to watch what I eat but it was actually pretty good. I would say if I was in the area I come back here to try some other things from this place. The staff were very nice and patient.

Amazing service and great food!!! The salad bar alone is a meal on itself.. And the rolls with the butter are to die for...
Great place kids friendly excellent service. The steaks were good made Perfect to order.  The fajitas are good be ready for a lot of food!! But make sure to leave room for dessert!!! :) definitely would come back when in the area again.

The nightmare started in July 2017 when their sales rep Skip walked into our door.  

At the time,  we were looking for a solution to replace our 14-year-old tile shower, which started to have molds just around June 2017.   

Skip promised premium product (above industry standard quality) and premium service.    He promised that Installation would be done in 2 days and we would not have mold ever again.    he also promised a life-time warranty of their showers.    and a premium price.  

Our child was 7 months old.  so we wanted it done quickly and we accepted the premium price.   

However, the premium price was true.   Everything else is questionable.   They promised the work would be done in 2 days.   Well, it actually took 2 months to finish.   because first they did not even order the shower door when they came for installation.  Then they ordered the wrong size and wrong material.  we did not want to shop around too much so we bit the bullet.   However, during these 2 months time, we could not use this shower.  

there were quite a lot of unpleasant dealings even before the work was finished.  I would not share the aggravation with everyone here.   We went on with them in good faith.   

Anyway, upon installation, they left us a two page instruction about cleaning and maintenance.   basically, if we use a sponge, the warranty will be violated； if we use any spray, the warranty is violated; if we use certain brand of soap, the warranty is violated.    the only thing allowed is soft clothes with Dawn dish soap.    And after every shower, use squeezy, and hot water to clean off.       We were joking that we would become the indentured servants to the shower when we first read it.   

after the installation, with the very first usage, one corner leaked immediately.   Their technician came and fixed it.   within a month of usage, mold started.  their technician came and fixed it.   Another month came,  mold came back again.   We have been in this cycle until now.    every time there is a repair, we could not use this shower.    We got so tired of it that we reduced the usage of this shower by 50%.   

so what is going on?  after all the care and extra maintenance, why do we still have mold?    if a 'solution' put us back to ground zero, what is it then?    When we asked the company, we were told that our house had mold.    This statement cannot be true because we have 3 other showers including one in the basement that is also used daily and all of them are fine.    A third party investigation proves that our house does not have mold.    Now they asked us to sign an agreement that they would recaulk one more time, then we will have to pay for anymore repair in the future.      they also implied that we were unclean therefore our shower would have mold.      

However, we have 3 other older bathrooms and they are fine.  We also have a cleaning lady.     What about there might be some design/materials/quality issues with their products.  

this letter was the last straw.     

i want to apologize for the 4-star review i gave them before.    i am sorry if i mislead anybody into using them.    

Please do yourself a favor: do not use this company.   Shop around a little (Our youngest child was 7 months old then. we didnot.).  A shower should not rule your life.     you really do not want to see the shower guy and call their front desk on a monthly basis.

We got shrimp pho which came with a lot of shrimp and tasted good. They have shrimp & broccoli on the menu so we asked for no broccoli and they were fine with the substitution. I tried the broth before my wife put stuff in it and it was nice. Not the best I've had but a good rendition.

I had the classic bahn mi. I'm pretty sure they were using a Del Buono's roll instead of a French baguette but it worked. And that's common around here to substitute an Italian roll due to availability.

Summer rolls were good as well.

So, because we love Patrick, and Dave the bartender, we came back. Chef Scott has redeemed himself. The pork carnitas, House made refried beans and pork flat bread were wonderful! Bravo!! This is the Patrick's Kitchen and Drinks that we know and love.

After being underwhelmed 3 years ago when my sister visiting from out of town wanted to go there, I had lunch with a friend 3 days ago, who also inexplicably selected this dump. I suggest it be closed down for lack of interest by staff and customers. It just has the feeling of being a long neglected operation. The saving grace for me were adequate wings on the "Pay for 10 and Get 20" Tuesday special. Nothing to make these any better than what you might get at a Walmart! And having ordered the mildest, I was not pleased to have heartburn the rest of the night.  My friend ordered 8 Naked Wings, and my God, when it was served it looked like a tidy little basket of dog doo doo! He left 3 of them, and I unwisely took them home to sample. Tasteless lumps of something (didn't taste like chicken!). The servers acted as if they were serving prison time. I will not go back.

Very disappointing. 
My first grouper sandwich had a small piece of stale fish, a single small slice of tomato, and lettuce. It did not taste like fish and had an off taste. The replacement sandwich was fine with fish that tasted good. 

 The first batch of  fried scrimp were almost dripping in grease. INEDIBLE. 
The shrimp appeared to have been frozen and were flattened, not plump.
 
The replacement fried shrimp were less greasy. Obviously the oil was not at the correct temperature for frying the shrimp.

French fries were very good. 

Waitress was good, but if she notified management, they did not respond. Having to send 2 of the more expensive items back, leaving us disappointed, will not generate good reviews. 

We will never return. 

The "municipal" paid ($4/hr, 24/7) parking next to the restaurant makes no provision for handicapped drivers. One would think that a "municipal" lot would have handicapped parking spaces.

Allen is a great guy with a beautiful boat.  He took us around the area.  We snorkeled around an old army building that's no longer a building but cement blocks.  As we requested he then took us to a remote island where we had lunch and found some beautiful shells.  After that we went water skiing and had an amazing time!  We've never water skied in the ocean so it was even more of a treat!  This was a wonderful experience that you should defiantly do!  Nice job Allen and we wish you great success!

Family breakfast here. The food was good. However the prices are outrageous. We did get a $15 off coupon with our hotel stay. I understand the prices being higher as you are in Niagara, however they also charge a %10 fee for business improvement. Which we had removed from our bill. As the manager said it was mandatory but did not want us leaving unhappy. The service was good. But for a 5 minute drive to Niagara on the lake. There are much better and affordable breakfast options.

Excellent pizza in Wayne. The menu is small, which means they really concentrate on the quality of the things they do make.

All pizzas are 12". We ordered one white pizza and one margherita, and it was plenty for two adults and two kids (11 and 9). Service was good, too. It wasn't too busy when we went, so I don't know how the service is when the restaurant is packed.

Let me begin by saying this was my third try ( 2 other attempts at other places) to get an 18inch dishwasher that I wanted. This store was amazing. I called and asked if they had it in stock and they did where as the other two places needed it shipped and then it would take 6 weeks. They gave me an excellent deal on the price and installation without an argument. I received the receipt in the mail the next day,

Come installation day ( only 3 days after the purchase) the installer called multiple times. He called in the morning to confirm the appt with me. He called around 12:30 to confirm he was still coming ( our appt window was 12-4). He called at 3:30 to say he was on his way and about 3:45 he called and said he was outside.

I would highly recommend this store to anyone and will go back for future purchases.
Food is okay but service was poor. They can't handle the volume. Entrees were brought out 20 min apart. Manager did nothing.
Deserts are to die for, steaks are great but I have had better in this price range. A Tampa must.

I can only write about their Elote asada (corn) since that is what my friend had recommended me to try. And man it was good! The corn easily came right off the cob with each bite and the seasonings that came with it complemented the corn very well. My friend said that the corn is one of the only things worth getting here since their other food items didn't quite satisfy her taste. But the place was packed when I came and people seemed to have been enjoy their food and time at the restaurant. Next time I'm in Philly, I'll have to come back and try a few other things on their menu, but I highly recommend the corn ($3)! 
Parking wasn't also too bad since we found parking right across the street. When it does get crowded, seating can be limited. My party was fortunate enough to put together tables to accommodate all 7 of us.

A funny thing happened while shopping... After enjoying dim sum in Chinatown, we took our adventurous American friend to this Asian grocery store in the basement... as he bounded down the stairs into a murky, poorly lit atmosphere, the sights and scents of the protein section were augmented and concentrated by the underground, claustrophobic location and lack of powerful (or really any) ventilation.  Once he laid his eyes on the living, hopping, crawling, and non-living exotic proteins found in such an emporium, our friend promptly turned a bit green and made his way back up the stairs - rather more slowly and less steady than he made his brave descent into this lair.

We, however, enjoyed giggling at our friends discomfort and picked up the Asian ingredients we needed.  Job done, we headed home, and everyone (including our good friend) had a nice chuckle.

MAAAAAAAAD MEX

This is a favorite drunchies/hangout spot for both college students and real people alike. How could you say no to their $7 Big Azz Margaritas?? They don't taste overwhelmingly loaded when you start sipping, but things get blurry reallll quick. You can get them on the rocks or in slushie form, and there are a ton of flavors available. My favorite is mango/lime! Happy hour for these ginormous drinks is from 4:30-6:30 as well as 10pm onwards. 

Hold up there's more. They also have student deals starting from 11pm, including chicken wings, nachos, burritos, salads, etc. Basically all late night foods one dreams of. I recommend the wings in San Francisco (hot pepper and honey), nachos, and the Barbacoa burrito. Mad Mex has great options and hits the spot no matter what you're craving. 

Everything about this place is solid, and I especially appreciate that it's open until 2am. Good memories are made here!
Great food! I highly recommend the "John Wick". Great price and people!!! All you can eat deal is worth it if you love sushi.

I can't understand why this place isn't slammed at every minute.  It's delicious, quick, affordable and creative.  I love this place, it's amazing.  The bao is tender, the potstickers are everything I want them to be and the sauces are great.  

Vegetarians will find some goodness here.  I certainly have.  The meat eaters in my life are also thrilled with the chicken options as well.  You just can't really go wrong.

Been  here often.  The atmosphere is awesome.  The food is usually quite good.  Wasn't super impressed with the oysters Rockefeller the other day.  The scallops and escargot are great!  The drinks are very expensive but usually good.  The other night we ordered two dirt grey goose martinis.  We ordered them entirely different.  I like mine very wet and medium dirty. My husband asked for slightly wet and slightly dirty.  We watched from our bar table as the bar tender made BOTH drinks in the same shaker all at once and gave them to the waitress to deliver.  For $14 each this is totally in acceptable.   At any price it is.  My husband rarely sends stuff back but I insisted.   He asked the bar tender to add more vodka rather than ask for a new drink altogether  and he was given a huge attitude about it.  Unacceptable to say the least.  A real bummer as it is usually one of our semi regular places - behind Ruth's chris (amazing bar tenders!) and barbacoa .
Family friendly.  Great donuts! Good brisket tacos. Also great margaritas(pitcher specials on Wednesdays)

Give it a try. You want be disappointed. Pulled BBQ Chicken, baked beans, corn casserole, greens excellent. Try the lunch buffet. All forementioned plus pulled pork, chicken, mac cheese, fried apples etc. Tradional, warm pub feeling. Friendly staff & owner, Judge stopped by our table for our thought on resturant. 

Great place for lunch...just wish they were open for dinner. To far for lot of our friends for lunch.

Family decided to try their All-You-Can-Eat BBQ. First off the table were sticky and the whole place felt dirty.  As we sat waiting to place our order, I guess this was the perfect time for the staff to sweep the floor right under our table as we sat there... Wished they had cared more about the dirty table top they sat us at.  We order and get our food. The "BBQ" chicken was baked till dry and had an odd BBQ sauce drenched all over it, The Beef ribs were 80% fat, probably boiled and also drenched in the odd tasting BBQ sauce, The corn muffin was cold and the coleslaw warm.  The only thing on the plate that was worth eating were the french fries. The only redeeming quality was that even though this was "All-You-Can-Eat" we were never offered more.  We wont be going back.

Consistently and reliably the best comedy in Philly. Actually, some of the best comedy anywhere. Their sketch comedy is by far my favorite night out in Philly, intelligent, creative, unique, and very, very funny. Their variety and improv shows are also very fun. It's my one go to place when I have friends and visitors from out of town. Without hesitation, I recommend PHIT Comedy any night of the week.

Well , we decided to hold off on Maui. Too many changing rules to allow plans. 

So Road trip USA.  

And maps are free here for members. We have been AAA for over 25 years. Myself , I had it in High School. That makes it 50 years, with gaps. 
And 100 mile towing, and they insure our cars and home. 
Guess I m all in. 

Glad I came , short line doing similar requests.

As no suprise i give this place 5 stars.  The idea of this place is so unique and something I could really appreciate for the tampa area. I had been wanting to come here and didn't get the chance until today. When I walked in it was extremely clean and really simply but nicely decorated. They have a huge board of options! Luckily for yelp pictures I ordered the mini pancakes with chocolate drizzle, rainbow sprinkles & powdered sugar! I also ordered a iced vanilla latte and let me tell you!! It was out of this world. I will be back a million times more and be sure to tell all of my clients & friends about this place! The owner was EXTREMELY friendly and made sure everything was good by coming up to us! Great customer service, quality, taste, everything!

We had tickets to a movie at just-one-parking-lot-over South Edmonton Cineplex Theatre for 10:45 but the whole date night was kind of a spur of the moment sort of thing, so at around 9 PM, we had some time to kill.

Most stores here are closed before 9 and we had just come from ice cream so we didn't need to go grab food. Indigo stayed open until 10 which worked just fine for us.

We wandered around for a bit but since we'd both brought library books with us, to be honest, we weren't interested in buying anything. We saddled up to a table at Starbucks (in the middle of the store) and chilled out there until 10.

Warm, filled with books, with hot coffee to go. No complaints here!
Great food, nice bar menu w varied options. Atmosphere is not stuffy so it's easy to have a fun night out. Bartender is legendary.
Many options, nice- spacious outdoor seating area, generous servings and sweet staff.

Easy to park, but the beach is very shallow that you can't enjoy it. You can't get deep enough due to signage prohibiting swimming. You basically have to be on your knees all the time.
Otherwise the water is warm although full of weeds
Ordered delivery from here for the first time.  Holy crap it came fast.  The food was piping hot, and delicious.  I highly recommend it.

I went here for their new weekend brunch and let me just tell you- RUN DON'T WALK. The tater tot hash browns might just be my new favorite thing in town. I had the eggs and avocado on toast and it was so perfectly done. And the drinks are incredible! I had the one night stand and not only was it much larger than I expected, it was so good! Definitely a new can't miss brunch spot for Nashville!

Tried Pork Intestines with Chilli Hot Pepper , Pickled Cabbage with Fsh Fillet and Ma Po To Fu..... Chongqing style food , but you tell the waitress your spicy level.

Intestine kind of chewy, hard to chew, needs to be tender cooked. 

They offer 10% off if check in by Yelp, so it is still very good deal.

Delicious and our server was delightful! 

We had the chicken chorizo tostada (a meal in itself), the June salad (very spicy), a taco that starts with an "h" (a great mix of flavors), the queso and the guac. Let's just say that my wife and I left plenty full AND left plenty on the table. Apparently they are growing in to a chain. I hope they keep the same quality.

I think that everybody should visit this place. Great food, beer, etc.Great prices too.
I am always amazed when I visit this place. Additionally there are tons of other places to visit nearby such as Chinatown. If visiting from out of town, there is a huge Marriott across the street from the market.

There a large variety of decadent flavors to choose from at Popcorn Bistro. The selections are fairly priced, and you can even taste samples of up to 4 different flavors. I had a difficult time choosing which ones I wanted to purchase which means I will be returning.
Good sushi and other Asian hot dishes. Love the Hot Rocks, Diablo roll, and Beef Tataki. Kampai!

By far...
The single coolest restaurant I have ever been to!
From the time you walk in the door 
To the time you leave....absolutely amazing!

We came here for a late night snack. There was a line out the door, but we didn't wait long! We tried the char grilled oysters, raw oysters, and the boo fries. Everything was delicious. The grilled oysters came with slices of baguette to sop up the butter. So good! The fries were perfectly crispy and smothered in a yummy gravy. The hand grenade was also tasty and strong! Remember to get one to go!

Absolutely fantastic experience! Kim was our server she was awesome! Very knowledgeable of the menu and properly suggests drinks according to guests' taste. Will definitely come back here to see Kim again!

One word, A-MAZING! I came across this   hIdden gem from Yelp. It didn't disappoint.

My husband and I went on a Sunday afternoon. We beat the crowd because after we ordered our food everyone started to trickle in. I ordered the jerk chicken. I love that they offer different portion options. My husband ordered the oxtails. Also we ordered a beef & chicken patty to go. We are our food in the restaurant. The food came out quick. It was fresh, hot, and the portions were large.

I highly recommend this restaurant. For sometime we've been trying to find an Indy, true Caribbean  spot. Look no further, this is it. We will be back!!!
Ordered the Caprese avocado toast, The (Good Karma) acai bowl w/additional bananas both were so delicious & flavorful! Very content w/the portion size & price.

Enjoyed breakfast here recently. Compared to some of the other Patachou locations for breakfast this would not be my favorite. But they have several good options, including many gluten free. I personally enjoy the granola with yogurt and berries - it's wonderful.

You can find the chain of Ben's stores all over our region.  I've been visiting them since I was old enough to drink.  Suffice to say, a lot of locals think of their name when they are pondering over where to pick up some beverages for themselves or an occasion, and it is nice having a local business do well and expand for so long, too.  This particular location on old North Virginia Street is located in the same complex as the Bonanza Casino.  Easy to find with plenty of parking, you can quickly stop in and grab what you need, or browse their shelves for something a bit more interesting.

The selection here covers all the bases you could want.  Beer ranging from the big mass-market brands to craft staples to local favorites.  Plenty of wine on the shelves, and certainly enough liquor to float a watercraft in, handily broken out by type, style, and brand.  And while this is certainly not the place to find some rare spirit or artisan liqueur, you will almost certainly find something to suit your tastes, or even discover something interesting worth trying out.  My favorite tip is to stop in here to snag a bunch of the tiny airline-sized bottles of booze, as they make great stocking stuffers around holiday time.

Prices are really decent, pretty much on par with other stores in town.  Though make sure to browse and see what might be on sale, as you can land some good deals.  Service has always been pretty friendly and helpful, too.

All things considered, Ben's is a really solid spot that you can't really go wrong with.

Indy is always full of surprises! La Mulita. 

Before I praise this place. Let me say this first - this place is pricey for tacos.

So lets begin.  The ambiance is quite nice and romantic. The AC is adjusted to the 'Arctic' setting, so bring a fur jacket.

I ordered a campechanos taco, while it was delicious! It was $13 for two tacos and exactly one scoop of rice. 

Were the food worth the $13.... ehh... but it is definitely above average. 

7/10 would come back for more

I LOVE THE CREPES HERE! This is my number 1 place to grab lunch, and apparently everyone's as well (by looking at how ridiculously long the line gets). Both the savory crepes and sweet crepe are amazing! My go tos are roast beef for the savory crepe and mango strawberry with Nutella for the sweet crepe. Thinking about them is making my mouth watering now!

I love it here!  They have a great Happy Hour with delicious food and good drinks.  Happy Hour is 5-7 pm Not only are there happy hour prices on drinks and food but every day there is some kind of special. On Tuesday any flavor Margarita is 1/2 price all day.  
I went with 2 coworkers on a Tuesday.  Food is ordered at the counter, paid for then brought to the table. We shared chips and salsa. The waitress refilled our chips at no charge. 3 different kinds of tacos are $3 each for happy hour. The pork el pastor ($3) was delicious as was the fish taco ($4 regular price) Fish is available grilled or fried. 
The margaritas are excellent!  I had both the prickly pear and guava. Both had good flavor.  
Tables are available inside and out. We are inside due to lantern flies.  There are two all gender single restrooms which were clean. 
The staff were pleasant and efficient.
I continue to go back again and again.  It has a very reliable and excellent menu.  Neither you nor your guests will be disappointed.

What can I say, only that I wish I could take this whole restaurant with me to Arizona. We had the stuffed bell pepper. So good we had to take one for the road. Of course the large size. The roasted beet salad was also super delicious! Learned about Matcha powder. At first I ordered the Rejuvenator which was very good, but since I read Matcha was green tea powder and Because it held caffeine as in green tea I opted for the skinny g drink. The pastries presented a lot of gluten-free vegan options, but I would not reorder any of the 4 that I tried. I highly suggest you check out  "PROTECTIVE DIET.COM". And compare side by side the apple pie with protective diet. Make it you'll know what I am talking about. Plus their sweet potato pie and blueberry crumble are AMAZING! Thank you all for providing such healthy and delicious foods. We really enjoyed eating at your place!

Found this little place when i checked YELP to see what was in the local area. I'm glad I popped on by. It was a beautiful Saturday morning and the outside tables were busy so the husbeast and I opted to sit at one of the large communal tables inside after we placed our breakfast orders. 

Inside, it's decorated in a fun, ecclectic way, that speaks to different cultures. Mexican Dia de los Muertos skulls are around as is other iconic statuary. There's a warm and homey feeling that just exudes friendlyness and the locals seem to like the place.  

The food too, speaks of the love the people have for what's offered. I had an omelet with ham and cheese and some of their home fries, the husband had one of their burritos, all the food was delicious and well made. everything tasted fresh! And let me tell you about their coffee! It was AMAZING!

I'm not usually a Walmart shopper, but we just moved to Nashville - and this Walmart is very conveniently located for us. The store was clean, quiet, and not crowded. Prices, as always, were good. Probably won't be my go to place, but it's a nice Walmart! I won't hesitate to shop here if they have something we need or if I'm in the area!

This UPS store is what woke me up to the atrocities of the chain and how they operate. Like the average person, I didn't realize that they were independently owned and operated franchises. If I had gotten decent service, I may have never found out. I would see one of 2 people- a younger lady and an older guy. The girl was always lovely and sweet, and I enjoyed shipping. The guy...forget it. As soon as he realized that all my shipments were prepaid with no chance to make extra $$$ he was rude and, dare I say bitter. I soon realized that he was the owner. Well- guess what, Mr Owner? I now go directly to the *official*  UPS customer center. It's out of my way, but I also don't have to have my afternoon soured by the likes of you. Oh - and that goes for personal shipping and supply purchasing as well. Perhaps someday you'll realize that the customer has other choices. Best wishes to your employee- she deserves a better boss than you.

I think this is the best food in St. Pete. Exceptional service , cozy trendy atmosphere, amazing flavors and really high quality ingredients. Great beers on tap. The octopus special topped with chili oil and micro greens was SO good. Also, they have my favorite cheeseburger in town. Aged cheddar and BACON JAM with a soft shiny pretzel bun and truffle fries. The charred romain salad is a great dish also. So good. Never disappointed !

When reviewing my experience visiting Yards Brewing Company, it's important to preface how much I love Yards Beer. With the exception of the ESA and Love Stout (which is more of a personal thing than anything else, as I've never enjoyed ESB's or Stout to begin with) all of their selections have quickly become personal favorites of mine.

I've often visited the Brewery bar, which has a wide-open factory floor vibe to it. The pool table is free there, so my brother and I always grab some Brawler or IPA and go a few rounds until they close. I even tried their Chorizo Quesadilla one time (which may or may not still be available, because their food selection seems to vary) and was pleasantly surprised.

Yards is a great place to visit for a Growler, and you can fill it up for cheap if you recycle your old bottle. They also let you mix and match a case, which is a considerably better deal than getting six-packs of craft beer just about anywhere.

There was one day recently, I think a Saturday or Sunday, when it was inexplicably crowded and it seemed like the staff wanted nothing to do with us, as I had to bother them several times to get service. It must have just been an off day, though, since every other time the staff have been not only prompt but also happy to talk about their beer selection.

If you get a chance, stop by the one time a year when they have their ultra-limited "Cape of Good Hope." If you like hoppy beers, you won't regret it.

This was BY FAR, the HIGHLIGHT of our trip! 

We saw Bonner Black and friends: 
Katie Mae Smith
Taylor Matthews
AJ Kross

I was told about this place by a local so I had purchased tickets online prior to our trip. Approx $7 per person. + $10 food/drink minimum. Totally worth it!! 

Everyone was sooooooo talented! We didnt want the show to be over. 

This is their new location and we were told it was more intimate and better than their previous one. It was a small audience. Maybe about 40 or so people. 

Didnt order any food. Just got a drink. Service is good. 

You MUST come when in Nashville. Awesome intimate venue and exceptional talent!

This was our last spot on our pub crawl - I was so disappointed we didn't start here - the full table top was filled with a group that was eating pizza and stuff from the restaurant next door, it smelled sooooooooo gooodddddd.  Staff was fabulous and attentive - helped us with our selections which we all enjoyed the suggestions made.  Our friends teen age sons were with us so they were so excited to see the games they could play.  Great experience would definitely go again next time we are going next door for pizza too ;)

I had no idea what to expect from this place, but everything was so delicious! The grilled bread with sweet butter is killer. I went with a larger group for brunch, and we had a medley of omelets, hashes, and open face sandwiches at the table. My brisket hash was so savory and loaded with juicy brisket. The sunny eggs could've been prepared a little better, but the flavor overall was great. Definitely order a dish served with crispy potatoes drizzled with mustard, so good!

Warning, the food here is heavyyyy. 

For that reason, this place won't be my go to for brunch. Noord still is a fun, yummy place to try if you'd like to venture into another realm of cuisine!

Not going to lie, I was fairly excited when I found that a Walmart was being built nearby where I reside, as I normally go to the Stoney Plain location.

Unfortunately, my excitement turned to disappointment as this location is lacking severely in selection of products.  I'd rather go to the Stoney Plain location than waste my time browsing this location only to have to go to another location due to lack of product.

Would not recommend this location at all.
This place is awesome!! The fried rice with shrimp and BBQ pork is a must, the war wonton soup was delicious and they make a mean mai tai!

Outstanding! Kudos to the entire staff!
We had one overseas trip of two weeks and a one week trip for a family wedding in CA separated by one day!  We downloaded a coupon for a discounted rate with the condition that we needed to stay over a Saturday, which in both of our cases, was easily accomplished.  We parked in the self-serve covered parking due to the seasonal hail storms.  The drivers helped us with our luggage, took us to our airline or car depending on which end of the trip and were very courteous each step of the way.  Parking Lot 3 will be my preferred parking spot from now on.  Sincerely, Rev. Dr. K. L. N.

O.M.G!! Mouth watering and flavorful black raspberry whoopies!! It melted in my mouth. The crust was soft. The flavor of black raspberry was out of the world! Wish I had got more whoopies from the store. Definitely worth the stop if you are at Philly's Reading Terminal market. Even though the market itself was crowded, the store has a fast moving crowd. So worth the stop even if you are short on time!
Buffalo chicken dip AmaZing!!!!  Busy place but expected that. Great service and the best wings!!!!!

This place in no way exudes serenity.  There were four run down rooms and the place was old and not very well taken care of or decorated.  The door to the room I was in had a hole where the door knob was suppose to be so the door didn't even shut all the way.  I just hoped no one random would look/walk in as I undressed.  As I was laying on the massage table looking around in front of me, there was just a vacuum cleaner and boxes stacked up for decoration.  The music they played was typical, but it had a skip in it the entire time...??  The "manager" was incredibly rude and unprofessional and had no idea how to handle clients.  The girl who gave me my massage did an okay job, but shorted me 15 minutes on my 70 minute massage.  I gave it a shot since I was already there, but will NEVER go back and wouldn't recommend this place to anyone.

This place is fantastic. The people go the extra mile, the rooms are spacious, the smoothies in the morning are delicious, and the pool is refreshing. I love the small, intimate feeling of this hotel and would definitely recommend it.

Sooooo Update: THEY ARE STILL AWESOME!!!

You know what is even better than coming in to Ale Emporium for some delicious wings??? Ordering them for pickup and eating them anywhere I could possibly imagine!!! They are as good to go as they are in house. 

I think I am going to plan a lovely horse drawn carriage ride for me and my spicy bbq grilled wings and carrots with ranch for next weekend. Just the two of us. Romantic right?!?!

I'd always known about Sanctuaria and had always wanted to go there but never thought to for some reason. This past Sunday, the store I work for part time decided to have an employee party there and I finally got to check it out! I arrived an hour early by accident (LOL oops!) so I sat at the bar with Sean and browsed over the menu. The bartender (whose name I forgot, but he was really helpful) offered to make me a custom drink since I admittedly couldn't make up my mind. So many to choose from! I told him I liked rum and fruity drinks that don't taste too much like booze so he concocted me something that smelled of oranges and tasted AWESOME. I kept meaning to ask what he put in it but I forgot! Alas.

We were both starved so we decided to order one dish to try for each of us. He got the slider burger things with the bacon aioli and fried plantains and I got the Spaniard Scampi off of their special birthday menu. OMG. The shrimp was beyond amazing. It came in a garlicy shallot butter white wine sauce. Oh God. So. Freaking. Amazing. It also came with about 4-5 pieces of shrimp and 3 slices of bread for dipping. I liked that they offered to bring me more bread when I had consumed all of it and all of the shrimp and all that remained was dipping sauce. Mmm. I tried a bite of the slider things and they were tasty but nothing special and Sean agreed. I am not sure if I'd order those but I do prefer seafood, lol.

When our party arrived (20+ people) we mosied on over to the back of the restaurant. Man. I really dig on the decor here. It is SO up my alley. It's as if they came up with a Guillermo del Toro themed restaurant. SERIOUSLY. If you are a fan of his movies, EAT HERE. I demand it! :) Another note, the staff was VERY friendly and attentive. They did a FABULOUS job with our humongous party! They were running around frantically to make sure everyone got their orders in and food started coming out pretty quickly. I was impressed, needless to say! I got to try a couple of bites of some other tapas that my coworkers had ordered. I almost ordered the wicked good shrimp but glad I didn't because it was too damned spicy for my taste. LOL. I'm a pansy, I know. I did end up getting the chicken skewers and while  the grilled chicken flavor was incredible, I really didn't like the dipping sauce that they came with. It was sort of coconutty and had a faint curry aftertaste but the reason why I didn't like was because it was too spicy again! I think you can totally find good eats at Sanctuaria if you don't like spicy food, just make sure you ask your server or bartender for suggestions. You won't be disappointed! I wanted to ask for suggestions but they were trying so hard to get everyone's order in so I just went for the chicken randomly. Next time I will ask, hehe. The chef did come out to check up on us which I thought was a nice touch. I asked him for a non spicy dipping sauce and he gladly brought some bacon aioli dipping sauce--mmm!

As a little bonus, they brought us free cookie cake thingies since it was their anniversary/birthday. Cute touch! I will definitely be back to Sanctuaria. I am so glad it's close to where I live!!

First Timer here and it was the best breakfast I've had in Nashville.  I got the basic... eggs, potatoes, sausage, and toast.  Usually you have to add some sort of condiment to your potatoes or eggs due to lack of flavor, however they don't hold back on flavor/seasoning.

Besides the meal being exceptional, its really the culture at the restaurant that makes it feel homey and comfortable.  Lastly, the price was phenomenal for Germantown - aka what breakfast should cost today.

One of the prettiest restaurants in Philadelphia. 

The lobster roll is delicious and the burger was really tasty. Farro salad was decent. 

Service was friendly but slow. A nice spot to come kill some time, enjoy your coffee, take in the atmosphere.

Ripped off! The server triple charged me and I have yet to see my debit card refunded after I caught the mistake and reported this to management.  When they tried to correct the mistake they just kept charging my card.  My coworkers with me also were charged wrong and had to dispute there cards being ran multiple times.  
I do like the food.  I'll just bring cash next time.  I hope they won't  screw that up.

Had another excellent experience again at Tampa Floats. Much improved shower head in the room I was in (not the super, too low flow one from the first time).  I like the low key welcome and ease of getting started.  In order to keep the pod from getting too cool it is important to keep it closed.  I opened it a few times for my first float.  I noticed a difference by keeping it closed the entire time this time.

We stayed here for a half week, choosing this location due to its proximity to the convention center. Check in was quick and easy, and the front desk clerks were friendly and always very polite. 

There is a nice little courtyard, with an impressive looking gas grill, pool, basketball court, seating/lounging area, and walkway. There is a tiny dog park here off to the side for those that bring their dogs.

Amenities also include a basic fitness room, open 24/7, and free wi-fi. There is a hot breakfast in the mornings which I enjoyed. Each day they had such items as scrambled eggs, 2 types of sausage, grits, oatmeal, waffles, and potato pancakes. For drinks there was soda, water, coffee, tea, and juice.

While the hallway to our room smelled musty and felt damp, our room was fine (We got the standard king size room). There are 2 TVs in the room, one in the living room and 1 in the bedroom. The kitchen is nice in that there is a full size fridge, dishwasher, microwave, stove, and all the kitchen utensils and drink ware you would need if you were going to cook a meal in your room. The room itself was spacious, and the bed was comfortable. The A/C unit worked fine, and the bathroom was very clean. Our room faced the courtyard, and while we could hear people playing games on the basketball court outside, we couldn't hear any neighboring rooms so sound retention seemed to be good.

This location is close to the wonderful Cochon and Cochon Butcher restaurant, so if you want some good eats, walk over a short distance and you'll be there!

Overall, a good experience. If I need a hotel room around the convention center again, this is the place to stay at!

Very very very delicious.  I had Aloo Gobhi, which is my favorite.  Mixed vegis Korma , wow!!! Pretty good (sauce is good and spicy).  I also had a spinach dish, dont know the name,  but it was spicy and yummy.  The  plain Naan was tasty, more like a thin pizza crust, my least favorite.  It didnt taste like the Naan im accustomed to.  My 4 stars is based on food.  2 stars on customer service,  they male behind counter was friendly and helpful, but he insinuated with his eyes and words that i was ordering to much food.  I would have been offended and would have asked for my money back, but i grew up in Southern California's Little India area and know how this culture frowns and looks down on fat, chubby,  thick, or anyone not a size 4 or smaller.  The food is good!

The food is quite tasty, and the service was attentive, friendly and informative.  And it's not exactly a "hole-in-the-wall" as someone else stated -- although it's simple, it's somewhat charmingly decorated.  The pastry appetizers (whatever they're called) were actually our favorite part of the meal.  The main part of the meal is served on injera on a large round platter.  The injera on the platter is suffused with the juices from the food resting on it, which makes it delicious but difficult to eat with.  Fortunately, they provide a basket with additional injera.

The injera is, well, weird.  It has a really strange consistency which I could never get accustomed to, but it is fun to eat the food with it.  Seems like this would be a fun place to go with a small group, as long as no one was too squeamish about everyone's hands all over the food.
Best new place in town! Great ambience and even better food you can't go wrong with the bah mi or bistro burger.

Terrible Service. I was waiting at the window & pressed the botton for service, the 3 people inside didn't even look at me. 1 was restocking, 1 was sitting down eating icecream and the other was washing dishes. Terrible. Do NOT recommend coming here!!!

Gotta say - this is my go to lunch time staple, for a few years, but sadly they have changed their menu and seem to be offering way less protein on their bowls.....so that makes me sad. So sad 
I wish my Uber Eats delivered from here...that would make life near USF at lunchtime much better....tangents, here is the food info~
The hot and crunchy tuna on spaghetti squash is LEGIT delish, spicy creamy sauce with crunchy onions can't be beat. My other 1st fav (depends on if I want light and healthy vs more heavy- although both are not heavy - but the spaghetti squash just feels that way- another tangent) so my Other 1st fav is the tuna poke on steam sticky white rice (I used to order 1/2 the rice, add veggies, but they won't do that anymore -- insert sad face)
My other go - to's if I am bringing home to the fam is the fajita or the chicken buffalo 
All yummy
If I would have reviewed 2 yrs ago it would have been a 5 star, but...

I wanted to review this restaurant which has quickly become a favorite since we moved to Hendersonville in September. This place serves Pizza with a capital P. This is not your regular run of the mill stuff. This is Elite Pizza. Every aspect of their pizza is delicious...the crust, the sauce, the cheese, the toppings. There is no wrong choice when it comes to their specialty pizza, but our personal favorite is the hot chicken pizza. This particular one just wows, and we make all our friends try it. Everybody has been impressed and the out-of-towners bewail the fact that they can't get it on the regular. Do yourself a favor and pick up a few pies from this excellent restaurant for dinner tonight!

We were really in the mood for some soul food and came across Butter's! We were excited to try it out. We both got fried chicken and baked mac. He got green beans and I got the cabbage. The chicken was pretty dry with not much flavor. The mac and cheese was okay although the portions were very small. He liked the green beans and the cabbage was ok for me. Everything looked great and the store is cute but the flavor was extremely lacking. Staff was polite as well. Probably won't return though.
By far my favorite sushi place! You can tell the sushi is freshly made to order as it says.

Visited gaslight after wanting to visit for years. Walk to the first building and it was locked, with a sign that says go to the next building on the left. No problem we thought let's just walk over. We get to the 2nd building and that too was locked. We thought it was weird, however decided to walk to the last building and try that door. We finally get to that door and pull the handle only to be met with the female shop owner (I assume) and hurriedly rushed us out stating that we were going back to the original building. She then asked half heartedly what were we looking for?  My husband replied we were just looking for now as we've always wanted to visit and we are avid antique shoppers. 

So we get to the 3rd building again and her focus was not on us as she was assisting another guest. At one point my husband asked her about a shadow box that we could possibly use as a display. Her response was curt and rude and she wasn't really listening to what he wanted.  She automatically assumed that we wanted to purchase her displays which wasn't the case at all. Even her response was rude after my husband sharing that we've been looking for a while. Her response was maybe you will find it one day. 

After spending 10 minutes in this shop it was quite evident our business was not welcome. This is really sad as I heard her state they've been in business 40 years but apparently every guest isn't as important as some. 

No worries we will NEVER return.
Good prices, awesome flavor. We had kani shumai ( appetizer- steamed crab dumpling), gator and pink lady. Was delicious and well priced

I used to box dye my hair a ton, and go for cheap haircuts! Well no more! Since 2014 I've been a loyal customer  to these girls. I refuse to go anywhere else when it comes to my hair. You get what you pay for when it comes to this hair salon. Sometimes a cheap haircut isn't always good. I've been with Katie and Sheena, both of which are amazing! Highly recommend any ladies, and even men to try this place out.  They also have online booking now which is handy! They also have the cutest decor and offer amazing products to sell. Huge fan of the redken line they offer.
My favorite place to come for lunch!  It's always fresh and super flavorful. Customer service is great....I'll continue coming back and bringing my friends!
Great sports bar with lots of TV, The Chicken wings are out of this world.But everything on the menu is really good. I like to go on Tuesady night when my favorite waitress is there.

This is a cute place with a comfortable and cozy atmosphere. It is small but they give you plenty of space between tables so you don't feel overcrowded. There are also a few tables outside. This place is nice but I wouldn't call it the best Italian in Philly. I don't think you can even compare this place to Modo Mio or Mercato.

Mini crab cake appetizers were actually pretty large and delicious. This was the tastiest part of our meal. These may be the best crab cakes that I have had in Philly. If everything tasted this good, I would have rated this place a 5 instead of a 3.

I ordered the Vegetarian tasting and I guess they alter it by the day since what I got was a little different than the menu. I didn't mind but the waiter never mentioned it. The Farm Salad is a typical side salad- good but nothing exceptional. The Risotto Pattie was fried and didn't have much taste to it- by frying it, the taste of the risotto was lost. I would rather just have risotto. Menu shows roasted potatoes but my meal came with kale and artichokes which were decent. The small cup of mushroom soup that came with the tasting was outstanding. 

My fellow diner got the Penne Ragu. I tried it and thought it was very average and didn't have enough taste. 

The bread that they brought out at the beginning was also very average. They drizzled a very small amount of olive oil on it (hardly enough to add any flavor). I much rather the olive oil be given separate and not already on the bread.

Service was ok. We were only 1 of 3 other tables since it was a Sunday night. The waiter could have been more attentive especially since it was so slow. It felt like we waited a long time for our check.

I live near La Baia and eat there fairly often. It's my standard go-to place, because the food is always delicious and it's reasonably priced. I absolutely adore the grilled calamari and the eggplant pasta entree. I agree with previous reviewers that the staff is not overly friendly, but I always thought they were very efficient and certainly never rude. If you don't have time to dine in, a take-out order is usually ready in 20!
Food is great, family owned and operated, they care about what they serve. Awesome customer service, their kool-aid is the best.

Who goes to a pizza joint and doesn't get pizza? This guy, that's who.

When I was invited to eat lunch with some Yelpers a while back, Theo's was the location they suggested. Excited to try a new place, I happily agreed.

Despite proclaiming themselves a pizza joint in their name, Theo's also serves up pretty good sandwiches. I was slightly reluctant when I read that the sandwiches are toasted for 15 minutes, but my fear of a burnt sandwich were unfounded.

I opted for the pepper jack chicken sandwich. The combination of fajita style chicken and pepper jack cheese on the white hoagie roll was very good. Although it came with chips, the sandwich was more than enough food. 

I thoroughly enjoyed my sandwich, but need to come back and try their pizza. If you're in the area and want a good, casual lunch spot, I encourage you to try Theo's.

For my wife and I, 2013 was the year of discovering Korean food and this was probably the most memorable of our outings!

The location is definitely a limiting factor as it is out of the way, but definitely worth the trouble.

We tried the namesake Bibimbap and King's  Bul Galbee, the BBQ short ribs. Looking forward to future visits to try more!

First time in....great experience and looking forward in continuing receiving Erica's help. It's a community room which I did not have a problem with....chair was to noisy when I got out of it.....I'm sure it was the chair and not me.....highly recommend

After shopping here last night, I once again remember why I have only bought groceries here once or twice in the past year that I have lived in the neighborhood. Most grocery stores may be priced high for some items but then are bargains for other items. I have never seen any bargains here. I will only go here if I am desperate. With the Italian market in the neighborhood, I see no reason to go to this Acme as their produce, meats and cheeses are at least double the price as the Italian Market and not any fresher. $8 for pound of very average deli style turkey is expensive and $8 for a pound of American cheese is insane. I usually buy my deli meats and cheeses at Wegmans in Cherry Hill and pay about half the price for much better quality. Literally, everything in this store is a $1-$2 more or twice the price that you would find in other grocery stores. At these prices, you might as well go to Whole Foods.

The store is a bit dingy. The prepared food section, ethnic foods and organic foods lack a variety of options. There is plenty of parking, but the lot was a bit dark and could have had better lighting. 

I would only suggest going here if you need to quickly pick up a couple of basic items, and don't have the time to go anywhere else.

The employees here do move a bit slow. I couldn't believe how long it took for the deli person to slice some cheese and turkey and the line that developed while I waited. I've never seen the place very busy so I haven't had to wait long in check out line. But if it was busy, I could see how they could run out of shopping carts, but I would be surprised to see this place doing that much business based off of my experience.

Yo dude, giving you 3 stars bc I don't want to mess up your rating. But for reals this was 0 stars, half your macarons had sunken shells or were cracked and aesthetically not pleasing. You gotta toss the ones that don't look good. At $2.7 each they better be pristine. I'm on my 4th round of baking them at home and mine are seriously way more perfect than yours and I don't even charge my friends for them. You're not baking them right or they're old and disintegrating? No idea but you gotta step it up to stay in the game.

The building looked nice and clean on outside but the second I walked in it was like walking into employee smoking area.  My nose started burning and eyes watering.  I stood there for a minute or two then turned around and exited as quickly as I could.  I thought smoking in a public business was not allowed.  Won't go back taking my watches elsewhere.

I love pho.  I travelled a lot for my work.  I have tried so many pho restaurants.  This pho place is soooo good.  It is truly as good as it gets.
Definitely recommended.  You will not be disappointed.

I had a great experience there when I had the flu and couldn't take it anymore.  A bit of a long wait, considering I was the only patient there when they opened, but everyone was friendly. The place is clean, and the doctor was helpful.  Friendly staff.  Also expensive if your insurance doesn't cover it.
Great place for breakfast. Had the chilaquiles with pork belly, corn tamales, corned beef hash, and chicken & waffles. Everythjng was outstanding, and the service was terrific!

I've been to this location many times. Food is good. This particular day, I didn't like the service . I ordered a drink that said it came with rose petals and as you can see no rose petals. I asked the server about the drink and she told me they were out of rose petals after she brought it to the table. If I didn't say anything she wouldn't have told me they  were out of rose petals.

The food was average service was terrible! Waiter never said hello just "what can I get you"?  We asked for bread and was told "you don't have to ask I'll bring it".  My husband ordered a starter of soup and it never came I asked about it and he said "I'll bring it out with everything ".  He then brought it out and literally handed my husband the bowl ! Bad experience!  Many other places to have a better experience.
Consistently slow service. Inconsistent hours. I once arrived an hour before closing time and was told they had just closed. Will drive 10 minutes to the location in the CWE for better service.

This is probably one of the best places to get authentic and good Indian food. Their chicken tikka masala melts in your mouth and with the naan it's even better. They do online ordering which isn't complicated at all. I'm not very tech savvy but figured it out right away. The only downside is their hours which goes from 11am-2:30pm and then 5:00-9:00pm. But overall it's a great place and it is very clean. It's one of the best Indian restaurants in Indianapolis.

I have to eat here every time I am in Tucson. Anything on the menu is scrumptious, but my favorite is the birria. I love their gigantic Sonoran flour tortillas. Ask to have your burritos double-wrapped since they are usually bursting with all that yummy goodness!

Have been to this restaurant inside PARX five times now and have not had one bad experience.  The food has been consistently delicious.  Never a long wait and always fresh and hot!    Servers have been pleasant and attentive!   It's never crowded except for when there is an event at the Xcite center.  The bar is really nice and even though there are lots of tv screens,  it's never so noisy that you can't have a normal conversation. There should be more people coming here not just when you go to the casino because it's better than alot of the restaurants in the immediate area.

My friends and I went to First Watch for brunch the other weekend and we LOVED it!! The service was amazing and the food was delicious! I ordered an ice coffee which was so tasty and sweetened perfectly! I also got the lemon ricotta pancakes which were AMAZING! I've never had anything like them and I can't wait to go back and get them again!

This spot was recommended by my barber and it did not live up to its legend. I had a burger and my buddy had a chicken sandwich and both were mediocre at best. The food here seemed extra greasy, yet tasteless. The servers did not seem very happy and service was not as timely as you would think on a Wednesday evening. I think I can do without coming here again. Nothing special but good for sporting events due to the volume of televisions available throughout the restaurant. 

3.2 Stars.

NOT a great first impression. 

You know that moment in the chair when you realize this person doesn't know what she is doing?  I should have stopped it right then!

My hair color looks horrid. Lines of demarcation, very uneven, funky ends, so not what I asked for.. ITS HORRID!! 

 She was dismissive of what I wanted, she was rushed, contradicting herself and didn't really seem to care that I left not knowing just how bad this looked. When I got home my husband was like, what happened? I payed for this horrid color! Now what am I going to do!

The salon looked run down, not very clean,  not as cozy or relaxing as I look for in a salon experience!

I'm so very disappointed!  I defiantly won't be going back!

Forgot to mention, my hair cut is totally uneven.. Not surprised, she didn't check it after she dried it.. Just wanted my money and to move on to the next. So frustrated!
Excellent food, especially the red curry duck. I cannot find that dish anywhere else, and I have looked all over the country as well as outside.
Hit or miss if portions or food is well made. They seem to conveniently be closed at odd hours or "only doing door dash orders". But it's Taco Bell so what do you expect

I love Yogurt Delight!!!! They have great options for people who aren't interested in having a ton of carbs or are lactose intolerant... They even have ice-cream but I truly enjoy coming here for the yogurt!!!!

I was hungover and hurtin' for certain so I needed some caffeine sustanence.  Thank goodness there was a CC's Community Coffee House right there.

I couldn't stomach anything hot so I got a iced caramel coffee in the largest size.  The lady informed me that it was great to get the largest size because there were free refills!  Yay!  The coffee was good and tasted of coffee and caramel.  What more do you want?  I also got some roasted pecan praline coffee to take back with me to enjoy at home.  They had a selection of pastries and candy as well.  Oh and you can get your King Cake there too, since it is the season.

Overall nice place, less crowded than Starbucks, and a tastier iced coffee.

I typically don't do chain restaurants, especially ordering a steak at a chain....but, I've been to this location about 10 or so times over the past few years for lunch. Usually by myself to grab a quick lunch at the bar.

I ordered the Flo Filet the first time and have every time ever since. It's ridiculously cheap, but surprisingly flavorful and cooked perfectly ever time. I honestly wouldn't believe someone if they told me what I'm saying without witnessing it first hand....but it's true. 

Service is usually pretty decent and the value at almost 1/3'rd the cost but somehow on par with the nicer places in Nashville is pretty great.

Lovely florist off of Manchester Road with a great selection of bouquets, plants, and other decorative items for the home. The staff were friendly and helpful when I came in.  I didn't really have any price range in mind, I just wanted to find a bouquet that is beautiful and one of the ladies helped me pick one out and explained to me which flowers would last the longest.  The flowers are fresh, the arrangements are beautiful and they carry a wide variety, and they have the most adorable and creative vases! The bouquet I ended up buying came in a cool reusable jar container with a cover and a cute design.  

They have regular flowers as well as some orchids and the great thing is, you can go there and pick an arrangement without having to wait even on a holiday! I came in the day before Mother's Day and had no problem purchasing a nice bouquet. 

The prices are very reasonable and comparable to the other florists in the area. Another cool thing is, when you come in you are immediately greeted by some lovely scent of fresh flowers! I know where I will be going to the next time I need some flowers!

It's such a shame. The quality of food is really good at shogun. The fish is fresh and the appetizers are delicious. The reason I give it 3 stars is not because of the food. The food is 5 stars. The waitresses are kind and doing their best but the owner for some reason under staffs the place. There are three people waiting on the entire restaurant. It's a shame because the people and the fish is good. Just the resource management is awful and you leave with a neutral experience at best

I'm in here AT LEAST two times a week! I sit at the bar and receive phenomenal service every single time! The staff is warm and welcoming and we always share wonderful conversations. The food is great and the portions are large! I suggest the biscuits and gravy and the BLT. My girlfriend came in for the first time, with me, today and had the chicken and waffles which were amazing! The chicken was fried perfectly. I'll be continuing to come by every week!

I guess I ordered the wrong dish here...
Most of the reviews look pretty good.
I had the chopped beef sandwich.
It was chewy and crunchy..,
I could not recommend it at all .
Service was good.
My hush puppies were good... lol
Not sure about this place yet...

Mmmm yes, this place rocks. Although nearly every person in this shop would probably fall under the 'kinfolk' / hipster category, you still somehow fit in. The customer service was not at all pretentious, and was very helpful.

My husband got some latte with ginger, and it came with a candied ginger (wish I remembered the name!). I ordered the same thing I get when we try new shops: an iced vanilla latte with almond milk (in CREMA's case, their milk is an almond-coconut mixture). Oh and it was damn delicious.

As we were leaving, my husband tried to throw my drink into the recycle hole, but couldn't fit it though. The lovely barista REMEMBERED his name, and shouted at him from the bar to push it in harder to get it through! She knew his name, even though this place seems busy all the time.

The only thing I was sad about was that they no longer make those amazing looking doughnuts seen in some yelp photos here. If I was a Nashville resident, I'd be here often.

They also have a ton of brewing equipment to fulfill your home brew needs.

Just left this location. Went with a friend and were seated. Waited for another friend to meet us. We were told our waitress would be with us shortly. We waited over 30 minutes and nobody came to check on us, give us water, or ask us if we wanted a cocktail. Our 3rd friend showed up and we waited about 15 more minutes with no one coming to our table. We ended up walking out. We passed the hostess on the way out who definitely noticed us, but she did not even acknowledge us or ask us why we were leaving. Bad service!

When I go to a Korean BBQ restaurant, Galbi (beef rib) is always my only and true love:)  

Tried Seorabol last Saturday, the Galbi is very tasty, juicy and fresh. Lettuce  come with it is fresh too.  And they HAS the CHARCOAL!  Charcoal is the reason that bring us in. Tasty Galbi+DIY Charcoal=a perfect meal.   
Two orders of Galbi is pretty enough for two of us.  And the waiter we had is very helpful and we like him. 

but, the soybean paste is a little salty. Hope it will change or offer a less sodium option. Thank you.

Management messaged me after my review. I made repeated attempts to message them back.
No one ever got back to me.

I was at Applebee's Brandon last night.  The ladies restroom was dirty and it smelled like old Urine. GROSS  This rest room needs to be remodeled badly.  
ALSO the appetizer plates that we were given were dirty had dried  food on them and a spoon that I was given for my coffee was sticky.  Someone is dropping the ball  or should I say spoon?

Brandon and I took my mom and her friend to Clearwater to see the sunset. We decided to come here for dinner. Mom and her friend had the fish and chips and thought they were really good. Brandon had the grouper sandwich he said it was good but it wasn't anything over the top. I had the mojo chicken which was also pretty good. Everyone was really impressed with the sides actually, mom and her friend had fries with their fish obviously and they said they were awesome, Brandon and I had mashed potatoes and they were amazing!! Overall it was good food and good service but it wasn't anything extra.:)
A bit pricey but tasty mini doughnuts made to order. A number of flavor choices and friendly servers in this new mall spot.

I arrived at Forest and Main on a Friday night right before 7pm. We were able to be seated right away and I immediately picked out the bacon popcorn for us to snack on. All the beers are brewed at the restaurant so I highly recommend going with that over a cocktail or glass of wine.

Next my boyfriend and I split the cheese plate which comes with pickled vegetables. For our main courses I opted to get the fish and chips while Scott got the burger. I think I had more chips than fish however it was was very filling after the snacks we had. If you are going out after dinner get a cup of coffee, it's French press! Not a bad meal for decent prices. I would go back again.

Very friendly folks offering great food at a good price. The Zha Jiang Mein and braised beef noodles are both excellent. Try the boba, too! Better to park on the road than try to park in the strangely oriented parking lot.

Great place for a tattoo. Professionally done, and the prices were fair. Me and a friend both got tattoos from kelsey and john, and they both are outstanding artists. You'll know the place when u see the logo of the hulk smashing through capt americas shield.

The Fox is amazing!  This theater is so gorgeous I almost spend more time looking at the inside of the building than the show I'm there to see.  As many times as I've been there, I'm still in awe of just how beautiful it is.  It's not cheap to see a show here, but if you have the chance you should definitely take it!

In my opinion, atmosphere can add or take away a star.  It's almost impossible to get five stars without a good atmosphere, so it's mostly required.  A bad atmosphere can ruin an experience, as some local coffee shops can attest to.  

An awesome atmosphere gives Nuvo Burrito that third star.  I loved the sense of humor, the whimsical photographs, the good wifi makes up a little for the very mediocre food.  Their burritos try to be wraps with warms fillings.   Quesadillas try to more like pizzas with their flatbread and extensive toppings.

Deborah was an absolute joy, and another reason I'm giving this a 3-star rating, but I'd much rather have a simple food experience that's done very well, then trying to create edible art that's just mediocre.  And Nuvo's food is just mediocre at best.

This dealership does not even deserve a star absolutely atrocious service a few weeks ago i went to look at a used car and made a appointment for 4 and didnt even get helped till atleast 4:45 the lady was working with someone else and i could tell they were frustrated with the service too. Next we try to sit down and talk numbers and she had absolutely no information about anything continuously went back to ask her manager which took atleast 15+ min everytime and would always come back with a dull answer. I put a down payment on the vehicle foolishly and said i would come back the next day or so to pick up the car and keep in mind i live out of state and as my appointment approaches she calls me and said my papers didnt match her requirements when before she said it was all set to go, at this point i was fed up with the BS and pulled out of the deal. Further along I requested for a refund of my initial down payment to hold the car and here i am a few weeks later and a couple"its processing " texts later without my money luckily i found the car i wanted with no BS at another BMW. I would highly recommend it to stay away from this dealer!

GREAT!

Sit at the counter and enjoy good food and good service! A WELCOMEd spot to the Dirty "T"

Tamara catered my wedding back in 2013. The food was wonderful and she was great at working with our budget. She offered lots of tips that helped plan our reception. Recently, I had a work event for about 100 people that needed catering. I was happy to reconnect with Tamara and work with her again. The guests love the food!
Good food selection & selection of brews. Love that they try to work with locally sourced ingredients when possible as well. Staff has always been friendly and accommodating.

I echo all of the great reviews below. I adore Kuma and eat there weekly. The food is always delicious, the fish is excellent quality, the prices are reasonable and the owners and staff are warm and friendly. I generally get rolls and my husband gets chirashi but everything is great here -- including the pad thai. We moved from NYC so we're sushi snobs and having a reliable neighborhood sushi restaurant is a must. Kuma fits the bill perfectly and we are so happy to have found such a great restaurant in our own backyard.
The chicken parm sub, fries and cannoli were so delicious! I ordered the food to go so I'm not sure about the inside dining experience. Food was ready when I arrived, hot and service was great!

Disappointed...

After hearing such great things about Council Oak from friends I decided to go there yesterday evening after I was over the casino. I debated with myself trying to decide on the crab cakes or the porterhouse, and eventually figured I couldn't go wrong with the steak. After all, the porterhouse is one of my favorite cuts...I ordered it medium and it took about 20-25mins for it to come out. The waitress asked if I wanted bread while I waited but then realized that they were all out for the night. Once the steak came out, It was completely over cooked so I sent it back. After waiting another 20-25 mins the second porterhouse came out better but still not the "medium" I expected. I was too tired to and aggravated to try again so I just took it home to-go. I figured my bf would eat it. Overall, I wasn't impressed by the service nor the food. It's not at the top of my list of restaurants to revisit, and I was even more disappointed that a manager did not come and address the issue of me having to send my food back...However, I will say that the band that was playing was pretty good.

Had dinner 11/11/17 With wife and adult daughter. No reservation on a Saturday night (6:30)and was seated within 10 minutes. Had the ribeye, wife had filet mignon. Wife asked for med well came out closer to rare as was mine which I ordered medium.  Other than that was a nice meal with a nice atmosphere.

ONLY GET THE charboiled OYSTERS!!  The rest of the food was AWFUL!!!  Save your money!!!  I got the shrimp, oyster, beef combo, all really awful.  My boyfriend got the crab stuffed lobster, the stuffing was COLD!  However, we did start out with the oysters which were very good, so stick with those!!!!

First visit and I really would recommend them. One of my peeves about going to nail salons is feeling uncomfortable while there and not once did this take place here, even after being in the shop for almost two hours. I don't have any complaints in regard to the job done either. After arriving I explained what I wanted and didn't have to do any voicing afterwards. Harrison even brought over various shades for me to pick from!  Going back on Wednesday for a facial. 

P.S. I enjoyed the dim lighting. Super relaxing. And they do use a light while doing manis if anyone was concerned.

It was dirty and there was a bug near our table. Not a small bug. A big one. I don't complain usually but it was on a whole other level of gross. The server was nice, apologized for the bug, and quickly cashed us out when we asked to leave.

Have been to this location several times for different jewelry needs, and each time the staff has been extremely helpful. They help me find exactly what I am looking for in my price range. Their prices are excellent and products are great quality. Very pleased with their lifetime protection plan as well- including unlimited cleanings. I would recommend stopping in and seeing what they can do for you. I have always been pleased.

One of my favorite Lunch spots of all time is Poca Cosa!  I can never go wrong with the "Plato": Chef's choice of 3 dishes, served with the best rice and beans in town.  (I really, really love the beans!)

The owner Suzana is fantastic.  She visits every table and makes sure that everyone is happy.  

But...what really makes this place special is Hector, my favorite server.  Hector has been at Poca Cosa for years.  His personality, humor and service really combine to make every meal at Poca Cosa something out of the ordinary.

So simple. They have it set up so you can email them whatever you need to print and you just pay 11cents per page. Fed ex would of charged me computer time at 49 cents a minute then 60 cents per page. I had to print 80 pages btw. So that was a total save.....Easy peasy. 
Thank you to the blonde women with glasses.

Believe everything you hear about the service being absolutely terrible at this place.  The food...great.  Beer selection...great.  Service - worst I have ever experienced.  There are 3 separate incidents where I was not even given a glass of water until 10 minutes after I was sat, but I'd like to highlight the last and most recent incident.  The host informed me that there were not any seats at the bar for my girlfriend and I and I stated that I did not wish to sit at a table because the last 2 times I did that, I was completely ignored.  She assured me this would not happen but did NOT know that I'd be timing the entire interaction between me and the server.  Sat down, and was given menus.  Asked for 2 glasses of water and a few minutes to look at beer menu.  She returned and asked If we were ready to order drinks.  My girl ordered a beer, I asked to sample one of the crafts.  Still no water at my table...we were seated at exactly 8:47 PM on a Thursday night.  8:53 PM - 2 interactions with the server - one to order 2 waters and one to put in drink and food order.  9:03 PM - still no water on table - no beers - nothing.  I went to the hostess to discuss my displeasure - her response was to now put 2 servers on serving my table...which consisted of me and my girlfriend.  Don't go here if you take blatant laziness and disregard for a customer's needs personally like I do.
