Miriam is not only helpful kind and knowledgeable but she also has such a great energy.  I went in with physical pain and by the end of the session it had gone.  And it is Still gone.  I recommended her and her services 100%

Absolutely gorgeous! I went for Sunday mass and the Cathedral seriously took my breath away! I had always walked past and admired the stained glass window on the outside and the inside is even more spectacular! The service ran a little long for me, but I am used to mass being 1 hour tops. Definitely check it out--whether you are religious or not, if only to appreciate the beautiful architecture and detail!

I tried out Fare for the first time when I had about 6 guests in town visiting me. I made reservations about 1 hr prior and was surprised and skeptical that they were able to accommodate a party of 8, while no other restaurant that I typically go to could not. 

I have to say that everything we ordered on the table was delicious. 

I ordered the muscles, which were huge and came with a great, tasty sauce. The chicken meatballs were amazing, juicy, and served with these potatoes and cheese that was incredible. 

Other things ordered at the table were 
-french onion soup (average) with some sort of cheese bread (which was amazing)
-salads (average)
-filet mignot special (DELICIOUS)

Everything was cook well, with great flavor. Will definitely be coming here more often.

So far, I like it...while not Starr-struck, I definitely like El Rey and will give it a second go.  The atmosphere is kitschy and fun and the service was good -- attentive but not hovering.  

The margarita was pretty good and not overly expensive; and, like the staff, it wasn't too passive or too aggressive.  The guacamole had a nice kick of garlic and there was plenty to share.  I had the chicken enchilada with salsa verde.  The portion size was fine for me, but for a bigger eater it might be a little on the small side.  The chicken was really well-cooked - tender and flavorful - and the salsa verde was tasty, but had been mellowed a little too much.  It needed more tang and just a hint more spice.  My friend had the short rib torta, with which she was a bit disappointed.  It wasn't bad by any means, but she said it was just a little too ordinary, more regular old sandwich than torta.

So, I'm giving it four stars based on my meal, the service and the atmosphere ... and perhaps mostly because I would like to go back soon to try more of the menu.  (And, another drink. Shh.)

We stopped by to grab a wonderful chocolate drink & reminisce about our engagement here. Josh made us exquisite Italian hot chocolate and an espresso chocolate milk shake. Service and drinks were exceptional!!! Look forward to our next visit

I've eaten here twice now (for dinner) and we had a great experience both times. Same waitress both times, who was very knowledgeable about wines and the food, and attentive as well. They were even able to accommodate our reservation for a friend who decided to come with us at the last minute, even though the restaurant was pretty full at 8pm on a Friday evening!

Food is pretty good, focused on French-ish cuisine using local ingredients. We were there about 4 weeks apart and the menu had changed somewhat already - not sure if this is a regular occurrence or if it was just the season changing over. In any case, it made me happy to have new options to try. The menu is a good size - enough choices but not overwhelming.

The appetizers have been hit and miss - crispy duck fritters where I thought the frying overwhelmed the duck taste (but my husband loved), frogs legs with spaetzle and a tomato-based sauce just seemed like an odd combination (though the legs were cooked perfectly otherwise), but the cheese plate we had more recently was a nice assortment (but I found on the small side for the price). 

All the mains we've had have been excellent though - duck confit perfectly crispy, a thick juicy pork chop (both served with seasonal vegetables), and a tender (but not stringy) braised lamb shank with delicious smashed potatoes.

I would say that it's on the expensive side but not as expensive as Normand's. A nice treat - make sure you make reservations!

I have wanted to try flour girls for such a long time and I did yesterday. We went in for lunch and sadly we were all let down. All the food was subpar at best. With that being said the lady who waited on us was very friendly and social. OH the HEAT!! It was so hot outside, hoping for relief inside. Nope! We were actually sweating as the have only one window unit in the cafe. I still have some hope and will try again but only for baked good. Also there display case was being worked on so the only goodies available were your basic brownies and such on the counter.

Five stars for the quality of the cocktails and the service, without reservations.  The "atmosphere" is a bit faux Los Angeles for my taste, however, and it's a tad of a local's price range for regular visits, sadly.
Friendly people. I love the spicy boneless chicken #11 and the red lentils with the teff. The tea is so good too and i can taste the spices which I like. The owner is also really nice.

In my experience with this business the customer service staff came across as rude. The staff member I encountered seemed disinterested and inattentive throughout the duration of our conversation. After which I decided not to use this company's services.
The best food the best service. All staff goes above and beyond. I highly recommend this cozy restaurant.

I just to run to this post this morning and write this review. A long time tourist of Tampa. Last night while driving around, my girlfriend and I passed this restaurant, which has a phenomenal display from the outside. The inside was really beautiful, great set up I must say. I have dined at a lot of four and five star dining, and this place decor is amongst the best. We were served that wonderful chip and salsa that everyone posted about. That was about the best meal of our night. We both ordered the chimigunga entree which was one of the worst Mexican meals I ever had. The worst I have ever experienced. The dish authenticity is gone. It was easy to identify that they have grown to the point, where authenticity has been compromised by utilizing box products over natural species and products to cook the food. Price for the quality of food doesn't match. Over priced for what they are serving. 

Overall, the drinks were good and the chip and salsa. Beyond that, this experienced will never have is return to this place. Quality should never be sacrificed for money. I hope this post provide a true evaluation for future consumers. Hope your enjoying Tampa if your ready this post.

Meh - the staff were also super nice, so I feel bad writing this... but to be honest the food was just "meh"... the watermelon splash I'll give em - that was very refreshing - but the jerk burger wasn't fully cooked, and neither were the fries... I left hoping I won't end up with food poisoning... Maybe I'm missing something here, or I ordered the wrong thing or caught them at a bad time, but I just don't understand the appeal... having lived in the Caribbean for a number of years I was really craving something to remind me of my time there... :(

MJ is a truly gifted massage therapist. My massage was relaxing and the pressure was perfect. He really focused on the areas I requested and did an outstanding job. Was very attentive and focused. One of the best massages I have ever had.

I decided to come here because I'm a student who also relies on clients from the community in order to learn about my field. That being said, I wouldn't recommend going here for a hair cut if you have short hair or want a short hair style. The student cutting my hair did not appear to have the educational background to cut my hair in the style I asked for. She asked her supervising teacher for assistance several times (which I didn't mind at all) but the hair cut I walked away with was not what I asked for and also did not look very nice. I brought a picture to show the student what I wanted, but the hair cut I ended up with was significantly different. The student and supervising teacher were not very friendly or professional. I ended up leaving in tears (which went acknowledged by all students and staff working there). It just honestly was not a very good experience. I hope that the student at least got something out of the experience.

This will be my second experience here. On my first visit, I had a massage and 60-min deluxe pedicure. Great massage, not so great pedicure. I wish I could remember the masseuse's name but I can't. It was amazing. The pedicurist spent more time on her phone than my pedicure and the end result really wasn't what an almost $100 (with tax and tip) pedicure should be. Not happy. 
Now to today... I purchased a Groupon for a massage and made an appointment. While on the phone, the woman scheduling the appointment told me to click "redeemed" to get a number on my Groupon. I did and the coupon disappeared. I tried to get back to it and couldn't find a number, it just showed used. I explained this as it was happening and this woman dismissively tells me to just call her back when "I figured it out." Nice. 
So within a minute or so, I "figured it out," called back, and not even so much as an explanation as to why she told me to mark it used, she coolly said I was booked. (The reservation was more than 24 hours out, what if I had to cancel it?)
So basically, a not very professional, dismissive receptionist, and past experience with the absent pedicurist may make this my last visit after I use this groupon, depending upon how the rest of the appointment goes. I prefer places I spend my money to actually provide me adequate customer service.
After the massage...
Nice massage after the knot-kneading was over which I particularly said I did not like. I'll be sore for a couple days.
So that was all written in August and saved my review and forgot about it.
I have since found other places I like better and with more pleasant employees. A pro here is they do validate parking, but with the massages being hit or miss, it's not really worth it to me.
I love Pegs. The gals are beautiful, bright and efficient, the crab cake Benny is my perennial favorite but everything looks delicious. It is a bright and busy, great way to start any day.

There is no longer a dress code at Ruth's. There were multiple people there in sweat pants, tennis shoes, sloppy jeans, etc. It's no longer the atmosphere you'd expect from a fine dining restaurant.  Service was great, but food was mediocre.

This place is old looking, needs to be remodeled & cleaned. They seat u in a stupid order. The workers look dirty , like they just got out of bed & came to work. The bathroom was horrible. The baby changing table looked so dirty like it hasnt been cleaned ever. They really fell off here smh

This is a small little shop but it is by far the best I've been to. They don't do anything fancy like massage the neck while your nails dry or parafin dip however it is the first place I've been to that took caution around my cuticles and I left with beautiful acrylic nails and no sore or cut cuticles. Everyone there including the other patrons were very nice. Also great prices! $13 bucks for a refill! I will defiantly be back again!
You get exactly what you'd expect by the looks of the place. It's a sports bar with good beer and OK food. Nothing spectacular, but serves it's purpose well enough.

I write this review months after the fact;
I had to drop off my dog for the first time just for one day. He had been recently neutered and needed to wear a cone for 10 days. Long story short.. I know he has separation anxiety. His cone when returned was bent, broken, and bloody. His stitches had come out in some parts and he was left with a huge bloody scab. My boy is a trooper, he doesn't show pain. They probably didn't know he had done all of that. I was a little ticked off that they'd return his cone looking like it did and not say anything. I can tell he didn't have a good time. Hesitant to bring him back.

Came in here for dinner just on a whim. Was told by a couple people that I need to stop here and I could not be happier that I did! This is probably some of the best sushi I have ever had! Also after reading some of the other reviews I knew to ask for the off the menu specials....also glad that I did that. The David roll was AMAZING! We will definitely be coming back here and I will recommend this place to anyone who asks for great sushi!
Only been once, but service was great even though we closed out the place. Excellent margaritas. Street corn is the best I've ever had, and finally the shrimp Arepa was to die for. Such a great meal.

By far my favorite place to have Indian food in the area. If you want flavor and spice, they've got it!! I always take my friends here and they rave about how good it tastes. I usually get the chicken tikka masala, saag aur paneer, Kadai paneer (super spicy!) to share, which comes with basmati rice. I also order extra naan. You just can't go wrong.
Good food and atmosphere. Can take a while to get a table but it's fun for the experience. Sometimes it takes a while to be greeted if they are slow.

Orderd a pizza in-store "to go" one night after a long day with no energy left to cook. To even place the order it seemed like a chore. Everybody was on their cell phones like they were just hanging out at a friends house and not at work. Disgusted I just paid the total despite that there was a tacky tip jar on the counter. My bf suggested that we had better tip just so they wouldn't spit in our pizza--that's exactly how those kids attitude seemed. Despite being employed they were looking for a handout and the attitude implied that if we didn't tip, we may have very well been given a little extra toppings on our pizza. F'ing gross.

We came here because we heard raving reviews! The one in the FQ was packed, so we had to wait about an hour, this one was a 2 minute wait. The dishes were good and uniquely flavored; I don't think many places offer what they do.
I got the St. Charles chicken and it was delicious. I recommend getting the trifecta if you want to try their top dishes.
The prices are on the expensive side, so it was a treat. Their pancakes looked amazing, but we didn't try them.
This is a great brunch spot, with friends, family, kids, or a casual date.
Located in a quaint neighborhood, it was a cute place to eat and conversate with my friends.

Dining here was truly a wonderful experience!  The ambience of the restaurant is very inviting and beautifully decorated, with fresh flowers as you enter and small attention to detail everywhere you look.  We had a reservation and were directed to a lovely, semi-private corner table where Karleigh was our server.  She was attentive, had a wonderful smile and was very patient in not only helping us select the perfect items for a special evening, but was sweet in not making us feel rushed.  

My husband and I had some friends in town from Austin whom we rarely see, we wanted to give them an unforgettable dining experience in St. Pete.  We enjoyed several of the appetizers, such as the fried cauliflower, tuna crudo, and Florida burrata.  They were all as delicious as they were beautifully presented.  The tuna crudo was my favorite, it was incredibly fresh and light, and the basil oil was exquisite.  We made quick work of our appetizers while we enjoyed a few beverages from the happy hour menu.  

For dinner, the table decided to split the whole fish, crushed fingerling potatoes, blistered snap peas, and squid ink tagliatelle.  The whole fish was a huge red American snapper, and it was the most fabulous fish I've ever eaten!  It is locally sourced, and comes topped with a wonderfully complimentary fennel salad as well as a side of salsa verde with capers, which is absolutely to die for.  The crushed fingerling potatoes are a must try- they are crispy on the outside, soft on the inside, and just a delicious burst of flavor that I've never experienced in a potato before.  The snap peas had a wonderful texture and flavor as well; 
 the diavolo sauce and crunch were a perfect addition to the meal.  Finally, the squid ink tagliatelle was every bit we'd dreamt of and more.  It was full of prince edward island mussels and baby octopus, and the house made squid ink pasta was delicious.  The sauce wasn't too heavy or too light, and was a perfect compliment to the flavorful dish. 

Our friends were delighted to find the wine list was so extensive and diverse.  They spotted a wine from their trip to South Africa, a 2014 red wine blend called "Missing Virgin" by Post House.  This was a fabulous, medium bodied wine with soft tannins, that is so fruity, light and dry- perfect compliment to our meal and such a wonderful find to cap off the evening.  We will definitely be back for this one on a wine Wednesday.

I don't think there was a crumb left on the table when we were finished.  We truly enjoyed every moment of our experience at FarmTable Cucina and will cherish the memory for a long time.  Thank you, Karleigh and the FarmTable staff for treating us like royalty!

So glad we found this place on yelp! After the super spicy disappointment of Saints and Sinners, I still wanted to give crawfish boil another try. This place's crawfish boil is milder, exactly to my taste -- spicy, but edibly so. And their shrimp boil was also really good. Fresh seafood, seasoned perfectly. What more can you ask for?
Great beer, great pizza. Friendly staff. An amazing building for a history nerd like me. Tables were all well spaced, employees were masked.

The phó was good but the service was not. I couldn't even get a real spoon because they were all "dirty". They took the hoisin, sriracha, salt, pepper, and sugar away before I was even done using it. The phó was actually good enough to go back but I will not because of the service!

WOW, just WOW! Hard to even tell you what we enjoyed most about our stay this week at Maison de la Luz. The attention to detail and all of the personal touches made this by far one of the best experiences in all of our travels worldwide. The Parisian flare made for an impeccable ambiance. The complementary wine and charcuterie board as you came in each afternoon (5-8 p.m.) and cookies in the evening (8 p.m.) were just a few of the things that set this hotel apart from the rest. The rooms are very large, beautiful and the decor is stunning. ALL of the staff is extremely personable and friendly and it felt as if they tried to really get to know you. The turn down service each evening was a beautiful thing as you came in from the evening out enjoying this awesome city. The Speak Easy and adjoining Bar were quaint, intimate and another fabulous touch to this spectacular place. We will definitely be returning to stay there again, just not soon enough.

2nd time at this great eatery for me and the misses. First we selected a few cheeses on the cheese plate. I think there were 6 different to choose from. We picked all the even #'s for some reason. At first we thought the amount if cheese was not enough but it was a nice start as it came with all these other items paired with the cheeses. The raw oysters were so good wish they came with more. The fire and ice is a favorite so had to get that. Then we tried the Branzino, nice and finished off with the ribs. I am not sure how they get them to taste so good? I could just eat a rack of them by itself if they came that way. Sangria washed it all down and I would say we were quite full. At first the plates looks small but after you share a few, it really is plenty. Including a couple deserts and the bill is about 135.00. Not your everyday dinner but definitely a place to take the wife for a 9th anniversary.

Ida Sekenova was fantastic during every step of my home selling process. I had never sold a house before and she walked me through the expectations and timelines with professionalism. She had an answer for every question I had and was always very responsive. She anticipated many of my questions and was very proactive in ensuring everything was in order for a smooth process. I never had any doubt that I was in the most capable hands. She was very knowledgable on local market conditions and set me up for success in selling my home. 

She arranged for an interior designer to offer advice on the best ways to arrange furniture and affordable or free ways to make my home more appealing to buyers. She also arranged for a professional photographer to take pictures that would entice buyers. These efforts led to a very successful open house and many showings of the home. When offers started rolling in Ida patiently explained to me all of the conditions and offered expert advice on the best way to proceed. Ultimately my house sold quickly and at a price I was very happy with! I will be confidently referring Ida to anyone who is looking to sell their home.

Walking by to get Thai food.  This place smelled so good we went here instead of getting Thai food.  Food was reasonably priced.  The food was outstanding.  I asked for more tikka sauce and the waiter got it for me even though he wasn't supposed to.  I'm used to getting my Indian food in Scotland and this place is on par with those establishments in the UK.  Very authentic food. Service was outstanding.  The only thing that needs work is the ambiance.  Overall I'd recommend this place.

I love craft beer. All those layers of flavor in a glass. Did I mention, I love craft beer. That is why I love the Casual Pint. Craft beer. If you don't like craft beer (or cider), you won't love this place. Unless you are into beer can art, as they have lots of beer cans. But the place does not feel like a museum at all, so you probably won't like it even if you like beer can art.

What there is to like about Casual Pint, other than the aforementioned beer? Very cozy neighborhood place where you could sit and play a game or two? Check. A bit of a sports poub atmosphere without the earsplitting volume? Check. Food? Check. No, wait, no food. Just beer (and beer like substances for non-beer lovers).

The only potential negative is the "to go" prices are higher than liquor stores, if you just buy a couple of beers. I suggest buying a whole 6 pack of mixed beers, as you get a discount, making it about the same price as liquor stores. Better selection than most liquor stores in town, so worth taking the time to pick out a full six. Or, if you like draft beer, take home a growler. If you forgot your own, they carry some.

I was in town visiting Nashville for the weekend and Little Octopus was recommended to me by some friends in the know. I'm gluten free and they told me that the menu had lots of options for me. I'm always wary when I hear this as that usually means salad or a burger without a bun. Snooze. Not so at Little Octopus. Not only were there interesting options when I went for lunch, but so many that I actually had a hard time choosing. Thankfully, my friends were willing to share (recommended!) so we were able to try many different dishes. All delicious! Don't miss out on the burrata salad with peaches or the avocado appetizer. The shrimp bowl with coconut rice was the perfect mix of savory shrimp and sweet rice. And if you can actually call a bowl of bok choi yummy, this would be the bowl. But it's not just the food that was impressive, the craft cocktails were a total treat. (Don't judge the day drinking!) I look forward to returning on my next visit to Nashville. Of course, if the owners wanted to open a post in Florida, I wouldn't be mad at that either.

4 stars, although 5+ for Eva & my gorgeous Ombre nails (see pic) & 5+ for Marie & my gel pedicure. Manager Mike (who "does everything," according to his staff) was abrupt & rough around the edges immediately upon my entering the salon, but he later walked over to converse, which was welcomed. He was very pleasant. 

The two friendly, dedicated, & professional women mentioned above spent from 1 PM until 4:40 PM on my fingers & toes. (I am happy I avoided the busy weekend.) I've never had a salon worker take more time w/ my toes; Marie gave each nail so much attention. And Eva was a pro w/ my Ombre nails; she made the process look easy. Beautiful work!

This is a clean salon located beside Dillard's; the entrance is on Paseo Dr. The salon has been here 5 years. The hours are CONVENIENT: seven days a week from 10 AM till 7:30 PM Monday thru Saturday, & Sundays from 11 AM till 6 PM. 

There are 4 wall TV's-- all were set on the HGTV channel. The massage chairs are comfortable. A blue plastic liner sits in every basin. I really enjoyed the surround sound relaxing instrumental music. Each nail station was fronted w/ plexiglass, & each offered a knee-level built-in fan to dry newly polished fingernails. 

Avalon offers many services. (See the pic of the 2 sided pricing sheet.) Services include Nail Enhancements (Ombre; Gel; Pink & White; etc.) Dips; & Pedicures & Manicures (including children's). There are multiple Spa Treatments such as Lavender; Green Tea; Peppermint Spice; Orange; Honey; Aloe; Chamomile; & Organic. (Mike requested that I not post the menu pics I took of the spa treatments.) Foot Massages & Waxing services are available. Facials, Eyelash Extensions, & many other services are listed. 

Staffers wear masks. Guests may choose to wear masks (or not). Hand sanitizer is available. Soft drinks, water, & wine are offered to each patron. This salon will even arrange a party here for your special occasion. Groups of 7+ receive 10% off. Gift certificates are available for purchase.

I did not award 5 stars for one reason-- "Add-On" prices. Prices here are higher than the four other salons I've visited -- perhaps to cover for the mall overhead. 

The Ombre nails were $67, which was a little high. But my pedicure was MUCH too expensive. This salon has more Add-On services than any salon I've ever visited. For instance, I was charged $29 for a Classic Pedi then an additional $16 for gel. $5 was added for French nails on top of a $15 charge for the floral nail design-- a total of two flowers, no rhinestones. This $65 pedicure is what normally costs me much less elsewhere. Additionally, my floral design was rudimentary-- far less detailed than what I've received at two other salons. $15 was simply too much money for the design & design quality. (See pic.)

Will I return? Most likely. Both women did PHENOMENAL work w/ my manicure & pedicure. Will I get gel French nails? No, due to the cost. Will I get a another design? I'm unsure. But if I do, I'll request pricing prior to any work being completed & I'll ask to see pics of previous designs completed by the nail tech.

We have been a participant in Hot August Nights since the beginning.  We have shown our car in Sparks every year except the 1st year. It's sad to see the small turnout this year.  The city of Sparks has knuckled down to the developers and built apartments making almost impossible tomorrow park your car for the events. I expect this in Reno, because time and again Reno has proven that the developers have Reno's city government in there pockets. But Sparks has always been community oriented government.  Greed has taken over. If Sparks doesn't open their eyes and take notice, the loyal participants are going to look elsewhere to enjoy the event.

My family has been hiking at Radnor Lake for 20 years; my kids have grown up on the trails.  From an easy hike on the road from parking lot to parking lot or stronger hikes like South Cove or Gainer Ridge, there are trails for all abilities.

We regularly see Turkey, Deer, Duck, Owl, and Turtles on our own and they have regular guided hikes.

They do a really great job!
Always seem to get a friendly server.
They even have vegan/vegetarian options!
Pretty cool.

Visit 1
Well: wow. I gotta say that my customer service expectations are pretty high and Firebirds hit them. For the most part, the staff was attentive. Don't remember having to ask the server to do anything, he was always asking if we needed anything. They lost a star because we found hair in my child's meal, but the manager promptly took care of it and took the dish off our bill. 

The food was delicious and filling. I liked the choices they had for the children. Nice portions. I have a 10 yr son who eats like a grown man and he was satisfied. So kudos.

So as I reflect on my first visit, I have to update and after my second visit. Firebird....firebird....firebird! I'm sorry buuuut we probably won't be back. I'm so sad to say that. My first visit was great (my husband would say otherwise) but he was willing to give it another go. This visit really fell short in the service department. Excellent customer service is really hard to find and I'm sad to say, Firebird didn't fulfill that excellent service we had experienced the first time. There realllly, really needs to be a overhaul of how they train their staff. It was fairly slow, so I figured the fa would come out a little faster than what they did. The waitress (in my opinion) could have been more attentive; made some recommendations; and known more about the menu.

The food here is pretty good! My fav is the Charmaine Corn only sold on Fri & Sat! It's a meal in itself! The crab Legs were yummy! The mashed potatoes are a must & next time I'm asking for Xtra gravy! It's magical! There's no signage so be sure to look close for the address or you will ride right past it. It was also hott as hell in there so we got our food to go. No masks worn just fyi... It would be great if orders could be called in. Curbside pick up would be great for those of us with little ones...especially during Covid. It's very small inside. I've taken 3 other friends here & we have all enjoyed the food!

Love these people!! They Came the same day to remove large items I had.
They were upfront about cost, got to work, and job was done. 
Would recommend to anyone who needs junk removed.
Thank you, guys!

Another awesome pizzadelicious this weekend!  Greg and Mike's Homemade Meatball pizza was a great addition to my Sunday night!!!

I have tried all the other supposedly premium pizza joints in town.  Slice, Naked, Theo's, NY....not nearly as good as Pizzadelicious.  NY is probably the closest and is my choice for a mid-week snack.  But when Sunday rolls around, Pizzadelcious is all that is acceptable.

This was our first time at Brother John's and not will definitely be our last visit.  We arrived at 6:15---having a 6:15 reservation made through opentable.com.   We were made to wait for about 10 minutes before being seated.

After we were seated our waitress arrived and asked us if we wanted a drink.  Since the drink menu is extensive, we asked her to come back in a few minutes.  10 minutes later she returned.  There were four in our party.  Two order draft beers; one a margarita and the other a glass of wine.   A few minutes later the waitress returned to tell us that they were "out" of one of the draft beers ordered.  Strike one.  

We then placed our orders.  When I ordered a Caesar salad, I was told that the were "out" of Caesar salads.  Seriously----how can you be "out of Caesar salad.   I ordered the smoked short rib fritters in place of my Caesar salad.    My dining companions all ordered a wedge salad.   Strike two.

When the wedge salads arrived, I was informed that they were "out" of the short rib fritters.  Strike three.   I was asked if I wanted to order something else, and I declined.

Within 2 minutes of the wedge salads arriving the entrees and sides we ordered arrived.  My dining companions had just started their salads, yet now platters of food were being delivered.  When I commented on the fact that the food should be staged to come out after salads are done, our waitress told us that they "weren't busy" so the food came out quickly.  Seriously??? What kind of excuse is that. 

I ordered the 1/2 chicken and it was decent....My dining companions ordered baby back ribs. As a side, I ordered Cole slaw, which was inedible----it was very sour; not your typical Cole slaw.  One of my dining companions said that his French fries were cold and tasteless.  

When it was time to end this nightmare of a dining experience, we asked for rib bags for leftovers.  It took 10 minutes for our waitress to return.  We asked for hand wipes----this is a rib place---and she said "oh----you want hand wipes??"   She had another server deliver four pathetically small hand wipes.   And then---to top it off---she forgot to bring our checks.  Finally, checks arrived and the bill was paid.   I dine out often and never regret spending money on well prepared, well served meals in establishments that at least pretend to value their customers.    This is something we did not experience and felt like we had been cheated out of what should have been a good dining experience by a restaurant that is clearly mismanaged.

My advice----stay away unless. you want to pay for an experience where they are "out" of many items and where the service and food is mediocre at best.

For some reason people rave about this place. Obviously, Yelp reviewers are the only sane ones here.

This is a great place to sit outside in the warmer weather (if you don't mind  all of South Street being all up in your burger) or for nachos. Besides that, I don't get it.

It is a small, dirty place in my opinion. They do have some great fries and nachos, but if you want real Mexican there are tons of better places. If you want a real burger there are lots of better places. If you want to get drunk, I suppose whatever bar your currently in will work fine.

Visiting from out of town
Excellent service, food and atmosphere 
Sushi was perfect 
Need to stop in and experience!

Great location in the middle of all the restaurants, antique stores, and art galleries. Close to Canal and Bourbon. Rich in history and haunted folklore this hotel is beautiful and very comfortable. Small rooftop pool and fitness center, great spa, and a carousel bar that moves!

Sooo 7th & Grove is a nice vibe! Love the fact I get to support a black owned business. The decor is filled with beautiful black art and greenery. I've gone three times and the music is always on point. The front area is the main dining area and the back is the bar / lounge. The staff have been very helpful and lively each time I've gone. I've enjoyed the food each time and will continue to return. I gave a 4 star due to the minor food mishaps. Definitely reserve a spot, as there is sometimes a wait but they do their best to keep the line moving!

What was ordered: Wings / Collard Greens / Mac & Cheese / Flip The Switch / Gouda Grits

Wings = Cooked as I requested - missed the extra sauce 

Collard Greens = Added some hot sauce + vinegar: that's how I like it!

Mac & Cheese = Yumms

Flip The Switch (2 Flap Jacks + Bacon + Scrambled Eggs) = The jacks were fluffy & good / the only mishap was the eggs, they did not taste good at all, not sure what happened there

Gouda Grits = None leftover
Great place. Line move quickly the attendant was friendly. I had a couple questions I am new to the area. The dryers were free and very powerful I was totally happy with my experience!

*ATTENTION TINA WRIGHT*
Fire Jackie and maybe I'll consider your business again. 

I brought my dogs in for their usual haircuts, and Jackie made me feel like I was a negligent pet owner. She had to bring it to my attention how dirty my dogs were! They needed five baths, she claimed, of course they're needed baths! It's all in the name Scruffy 2 Fluffy! What am I supposed to do? Wash them myself and then pay for their services? Then she went on to say what a danger fox tail stickers are by conveniently pulling out a Post-it note with one on it. My dogs are never in an environment of where there would be fox stickers from grass. It didn't end there. She claims my two dogs both have double ear infections and they're so matted. I would think if they had double ear infections there would be some sign of uncomfortable pain, but nope! And of course the dogs are going to be a little matted. That's why I go here. If I was a dog groomer I wouldn't need this place.
For my other dog I was shown a picture of how much fur they removed and told there was five more piles where that came from; I know, that's what I paid $75 for. Then when he got home he threw up a large amount of yellow vomit that looked like he was given something he shouldn't have been given.
My little dog looked very nervous and upset when he was picked up. He never looked so scared before. In prior grooming places he never looked tormented like he did here. 
After getting an ear full of Jackie telling me how to care for my dogs she tells me I need to bring them in more often. With her attitude? I don't think so. I'll take my dogs and my money elsewhere.

NATE, COURTNEY, CHRIS! Super cool crew, excellent customer service, vividly described everything with patience & enthusiasm.

I went in for a scone (which were clearly house made & fresh off the press)  Blueberry was the flavor of the day and I looooooooove blueberry.  So it was pretty much a wrap; I'll take an iced black coffee and blueberry scone please & thank you.  The place was nice and quaint.  Not easy to spot from the street so pull on the side road and there's a parking lot where you'll see Living Room off to the right.  It's a shotgun style cafe; plenty of lighting and seating along the window.  The patio was spacious with a few picnic benches.

I actually walked through the meat shop on Sutton through the back door and right over to Living Room; it sits in the rear of the meat shop.  They probably didn't like that but oh well.

Then all of a sudden I asked about the huge cookie sitting in the beautiful glass jar on top of the counter and everyone raved how it was the most delicious item in the place. It was a peanut butter chocolate chip cookie except it didn't have any flour so it was basically baked peanut butter.   I conceded... 

Got the baked peanut butter and superb iced cold brew and bounced.

I didn't eat the cookie right away but when I did break a small piece for the purposes of finalizing this review I wasn't blown away.  It was just OK.  Maybe it was the heavy Fleur de Sel they dusted the cookie in.  I'm not a salt girl so I found myself scrapping and patting sea salt residue so I could tolerate the taste and finish like a champ. I wish I had gotten my savory scone.

I'll stick to the script next time.

Terrible experience, avoid! Used to be a frequent customer, but will never go back. They forgot part of my to-go order even after the employee rudely assured me that everything was there. When I called for a refund of what they forgot, I got the complete runaround from them. People pretending to be the manager, then putting the actual manager on the line after putting me on a 15 minute death hold. The 'actual' manager, 'Ron', initially told me they were unable to refund what they forgot, but I could come in for it later (yeah right, you already ruined our dinner), then when I threatened to dispute the charge, the story changed to being able to refund it the next day. Then the story changed again and they left message misstating what they refunded, causing me to have to call back again. Barely got an apology out of them and was met with a lot of hassle and frustration over something that could've been very simple. Total lack of customer service, you've permanently lost three families as customers.
Baby ribs is perfectly tender, perfectly moist. coleslaw is very different but very good too. Fast service. Reasonable price. Parking is convenient at the back.

Toucan Charlie was able to seat our party of 9 when we walked in at 5:30. Our waiters provided us with excellent service and were so good about refilling our drinks.  There were a good variety of food- Asian, Mexican, Italian, American. Great deserts with pies, cakes, and gelato.

Stopped in on the way home.  Ordered one little burger and one all the way.  Probably the absolute worst burgers I have ever had.  This place used to be really good.  Not any more.  There were more cooks behind the counter than customers out front - and this was 6:00 pm.  Should have been a warning to me.  Let it be one for you!

What a cute restaurant, small and quaint.  Came here with two friends. We split a few dishes and were pleased with them all. They have great happy hour specials and the service was fast and with a great attitude.

These guys are terrific, I highly recommend them. I had to replace my car quickly, and Alex wound up working with me. He's great, patient and really worked on getting me into a MIni Clubman in short order on January 2nd for a the best fair price and good financing. Paul was also great. Terrific attention to detail and zero -- repeat zero -- "hard sell" to make a sale. They split commissions so it's just honest, professional business with no games. Paul even retrieved my EZ Pass out of my old car for me after I'd left it behind.
Best hardware store around. It may be smaller than home depot, but still somehow has a better selection, competitive prices and an incredibly helpful staff.

Tiny customer service area, you're not allowed to browse the stacks probably insurance/loss related, regardless it means you have to wait to get to the front of the line to ask the attendant to go get your beer, if they even have it. Attendant positively sneered at my request and told me "maybe go down a mile across the city line for that stuff". I drink beer to get a buzz and not blow my paycheck. Since I live a short walk away and just moved here I would have been a regular. Keep this snide crap to yourself or lose a customer.
Their dispensing water machine in front of Nona's has problems often. It either doesn't work or it doesn't give you the right change. If you cannot provide good service don't offer any.

Pricey fried food. Great service. 

Sent our order back the first time because it was cold, the second time because they left off the soft shell crab. The BBQ shrimp was well worth the heart attack that will surely follow if this were to become an every day meal. If you're in the French Quarter and don't want to drive somewhere better then go.

Worst massage experience I have ever had. If I could rate 0 stars, I would. 

In my previous city I got deep tissue massage for years to treat very tense shoulder and neck muscles that create excruciating tension headaches. A couple of one hour treatments has always done the trick and allowed me to go back to work/school. I spoke with the receptionist at Spa Solai about this and she assured me that the therapist she put me with would be able to work with my muscle pain. I paid for an 80 minute treatment and for the first time ever left in just as much pain as I had upon arrival. Not only was this NOT a deep tissue massage, but the massage therapist spent a considerable amount of time playing with hot towels and not even performing a massage. If I had wanted a timid back rub I would have asked my roommate and saved myself what, for a graduate student, was a month's worth of grocery money.

Horrible! Scammer.  If you place an order from this lady you're a fool. She sure fooled me.  Ordered and paid for 2 dozen for my daughters 2nd birthday.  She said she shipped them yet it was the post offices fault.  Lies. No tracking number ever.  Then promised me 2 dozen free cause she felt bad. Ordered 2 dozen for my nieces bday 2 weeks ago.  She communicated with me and acted all nice and said they'd be here.  Now I'm blocked from her Facebook page and have no cookies.  she never had to say anything about a free 2 dozen if she didn't want to do it.  Now not only has she ruined one birthday.. two! Bad business lady! Karma will get you.

Tried this place for takeout pizza a few years back when I first moved to Lutz. It's the closet to a NY style pizza that I've had here in Florida. I've continued my loyal business for a few years now.

      Delivery times have been more than acceptable, drivers have always been friendly, and have only experienced 1 mistake where when forgot part of the order (everyone makes mistakes). The manager handled the situation very well and seem sincere about the error.

     They've yet to let me down, and I hope continued success.  I'll have to dine in sometime and see if the service is as great as the takeout/delivery service I've received over the years.

We passed this restaurant on the way to our hotel.  There was a long line so we figured it had to be good.
By the time we got there, the line had dwindled.  This restaurant is cash only.  You stand in line, place your order and pay the cashier.  Once you've paid, you find your own table.  The line dwindled because everyone was seated.  So finding a table is hard.  We had the ham po' boy (what they are known for).  It was like any ham you can get from a deli.  We also had the shrimp etouffee omelette with grits.  The grits had no flavor and seemed hard.  The omelette was ok.

This is one place worth skipping.  Go to Coffee Pot instead.
Have been to just about every soulfood spot in tampa and must say that Fred's is a winner!  Will definitely be taking the family back again soon!

Decided to be adventurous because we don't have these in California...that being said, the menu offerings are odd and literally all over the map ie mac n cheese, pad Thai and penne rosa. I ordered the pad Thai, potstickers and tomato bisque soap. As far as authenticity, I was actually impressed with the pad Thai. My only complaint is the grilled chicken. I am no fan of pepper and didn't care for the pepper seasoning on the chicken. The potstickers are flat ? Tomato bisque is on the salty side... In short, it wasn't horrible but it wasn't the best. Maybe other menu items are better ?

We were greeted with a happy and helpful staff. 

The ice cream bars were amazing.

Going to come back and try the street corn some time ASAP!!

My FAVE snack for after a late-night of drinking...err, staying up til 12 at Study Hall since that's when the bars close in IV. The prices have consistently rose at Freebird's since I started attending UCSB..It used to be under $5 for taco's but now I have no idea how much it is. Pricey shit, my friends! But it's fun, social, they are open 24/7. And I never knew that they had bathrooms in the back, lol! There used to be a bathroom near the kitchen, and people would walk back there..until someone got drunk and locked themselves in. Then they closed it down and I assumed no more bathroom usage...But hooray- there are clean bathrooms round the back of the place. Wahoo! P.S. It helps to SPEAK SPANISH to the staff. They always gave me bigger burrito's when I tried to speak Spanish! (and I'm nice, that helps).

Update: visited for a second time last night after talking it up to my friends. I was so impressed again! We used the no wait app to get in line on the way, which I highly recommend! Our table was ready when we arrived. Our service was phenomenal again. We did have to wait a bit for service and the food, which we didn't mind, but they offered us an order of the risotto balls and dessert on the house. We were so appreciative! The risotto balls were fantastic - super cheesy, crispy and paired with hot marinara and a delicious creamy, lemony herb aioli. Perfect for sharing! I got the bucatini again which was just as delicious as the first time. My boyfriend tried the garganelli pasta with braised beef and olives. This was a hit! It's a super hearty, warm and briney dish with the olives. My friend tried the lasagna verde. This dish is complex, hearty and perfectly executed. I hate dry lasagnas, but this one had lots of bolognese and bechamel sauce. Highly recommend this dish! I do think they should serve it on a larger plate though. For dessert, we had the coffee cookies and cream gelato and "not tiramisu" coffee tart. Both were excellent! Thanks to Pastaria for another 5 star experience! I can't wait to come back and try a pizza soon. 

I'm not joking when I say I stalked Pastaria's Facebook page for months waiting for them to open. I finally got to try it out last week, and it completely exceeded my expectations! So far, this has been my favorite meal since moving to Nashville! 

First of all, the service is truly exceptional. Our waiter was friendly, appropriately attentive, and knowledgeable. I was so impressed. It really makes this place stand out! Also, I went with a friend, but I was pleased to see many families here. It's a perfect spot for date night OR families, which is rare to find. It was not overly noisy at all. They do have a children's menu also.

Before your meal, the staff walks around serving delish pieces of freshly baked bread that is perfectly complimented by the olive oil, chile oil and cheese on the table. Love that chile oil! To begin, we split the fabulous chopped salad with olives, pistachios, pecorino, pepperonis and red wine vinaigrette. I LOVED this salad, and the small portion split between two was a perfect light appetizer. 

It was nearly impossible to pick an entree! Pastaria makes all of their pastas and pizza dough fresh daily. Everyone around me had big, beautiful bowls of pasta, so I went with the Bucatini All' Amatriciana while my friend tried the Strozzapreti. The Strozzapreti is a more traditional Bolognese style pasta and was fabulous.  I was SO impressed with the Bucatini!! The sauce was rich, fresh, a little spicy and had a delicious smokiness from the guanciale. I would absolutely order this again!

Normally, we split one dessert when trying new places, but the menu looked and sounded so great here, so we had to try two - the butterscotch pudding with oatmeal cookies and the coffee tart. They also have a nutella fudge cake option and variety of house made gelato whose flavors they change our regularly. The butterscotch pudding was thick, creamy and packed with flavor. It was topped with a Greek yogurt whipped cream (they didn't say Greek yogurt but that's how it tasted), and two freshly baked spice oatmeal cookies. Loved this dessert, but loved my coffee tart even more! The coffee tart was not overwhelmingly strong, but it was creamy, rich and topped with delicious crunchy toppings (no idea what they actually were! Sort of like a homemade cereal) and a big scoop of homemade whipped cream, which is one of my favorite things! Don't skip dessert here!

I was truly blown away with Pastaria, especially since they just opened. We had exception service, and every part of the meal was exceptional and fresh. I've been telling all of my friends and coworkers about Pastaria. It's my new favorite date night and special occasion restaurant. I can't wait to go back! Also they have free parking in a garage beside the restaurant!

Four stars for a three star hotel. You can tell they go the extra mile or, very vigilant staff. Feels like a very safe environment. Also just such great attention to detail, beautiful Christmas tree right when you walk in. Rooms are very clean. If you're on the road and in the area, this is your best bet.

There are so many sushi places around here and I'm glad I found this one. Service, food and drinks were all great. I got the spicy garlic edamame, fisherman roll and spicy rainbow roll. They only had the regular rainbow roll on menu and I requested it spicy. (Clearly spicy is my thing). I was hesitant on fisherman roll but the cucumber mixed really well with yellow tail and crab. The cold sake I tried tasted great and came in a cute little can with a lid! Service was on point and great little spot on the corner.

FYI manager Carla that works at this location is a miserable person and likes to try to make other people Miserable as well. I live in walking distance from this RaceTrac to my condo however I will go 10 miles out of my way to go to another race track in order to use my mobile coupons without getting harassed or give an attitude or dirty looks. Coming from someone who has worked in the hospitality business for the last 20 years she seems like she is definitely in the wrong business. I have inquired with other an employee's from local RaceTrac in regards to knowing Carla at this particular RaceTrac and nine out of 10 responses were how horrible of a manager she is and what a bad attitude she has also... It's such a shame that I have to go out of my way to other race RaceTrac just to use my mobile coupons.Very disappointed!!!

Honest, friendly, professional, trustworthy, reasonably priced and thorough with excellent results! Ron is the only one I will ever hire for carpet cleaning! The first time I hired him to remove HORRIBLE oil paint stains (dogs chewed up my art supplies) that were all over my light cream colored carpeting. The stains were so bad I was very skeptical they would ever come out. Ron worked on them, the stains came out and to my pleasant surprise, my carpet was saved! The second time he cleaned the carpets they not only looked and smelled amazing, they even FELT better on your feet! Highly recommended!

Amazing food! Awesome service! Good selection of craft beer. The dessert was amazing especially the churro apple pie. Made for a great place to celebrate a birthday. Even if you can't stay at the resort which i totally recommend, you can still visit just for dinner!

I'm a CVS proponent all the way and this one has a special little place in my heart.  Mostly because the pharmacist was awesome.  She totally remembered my name and prescriptions after the second time I stopped by.  And whenever there were issues of any sort, she worked through with me, patiently and with a great attitude.  

Other than that, well this CVS is possibly a little more treacherous than the rest due to its location on Canal.  I believe a security guard and perpetrator died here a few months ago, but ever since then, a very visible security/police presence has been felt on site.  

Also due to its close proximity to Canal and the French Quarter - tons of wine, beer, and even a pretty impressive array of liquor behind the cashiers.  Reasonably-priced, no mark-up - which they could totally get away with, but i guess CVS being a big ole corporation with a reputation to protect, they don't.  

The cashiers can be a little incompetent and sometimes they permit a rather long,winding line to form.  Still, I much prefer this CVS to the three Walgreens in close proximity - it just feels more orderly and a nicer selection of convenience items.

Great smoked meat. Clean facility and good service. The portion may not be as much as you wanted it, but still enough. Bit pricey, but still good tasting food. Good place to go if you're craving for bbq. I'd say 3.5 stars.

We enjoyed our 2-night stay at this hotel. I think we were lucky that we stayed after their interior renovations had been done, looks like other reviewers got caught in renovation/upgrade chaos. There was construction going in the streets surrounding the hotel and the main entrance was closed but it somehow managed to be a non-issue. Construction didn't start too early in the morning and ended at a decent hour in the afternoon. 

Our room was clean, appliances were new and the wifi flawless. The staff, especially housekeeping, were super friendly and gracious with the few minor requests I made. The gym on the roof made getting a workout in very easy.

Breakfast in the hotel restaurant was great one day but the same exact breakfast was slightly less than great on the second morning, the only negative thing about my experience here.  

We visited here for business and would stay again.
Yum! Such a great sandwich shop. We are willing to drive the distance for this place! Love my city and all the great venues it has to offer.
Great ice cream.  Very cool atmosphere.  Smells amazing.   All good things.  Highly recommend.
We just moved into the area and have tried several  pizza places. But this one is NOT just ANOTHER pizza shop. It is THE pizza shop. The food is great, the service even better!

This was our dinner stop in Louisiana going to New Orleans (from Houston). My wife and I really adore Korean food and we'd always search for one in any city/state we visit (our default one) :). We ordered beef & pork bulgogi (to compare our favs from Sam Hawk in Utah) and my wife added their spicy Hae Mul Soon Tofu. For starters we ordered fried dumplings to satisfy our hunger brought about by the long drive. 

The side dishes are great and plenty. Service was fast, friendly, quick and easy. The bulgogi's had a sweet side to it compared to what we're used to back in Utah. However, we were delighted with the spicy tofu, it was fantastic! If you love spicy food, this definitely is an experience. The meat and tofu combination, plus the vegetables and green onions, make it a harmonious spicy dish. Definitely a good eat!
Just yes, yes, yes.  Had a scoop of spicy salmon and spicy tuna over half rice/half greens with ALL the veggies.  It doesn't get tastier or less guilt free than this. Excellent location choice too.
Perfect spot if you enjoy some great seafood. This place is awesome, and the food was delightful and the prices were very affordable. Rapidly, efficient service and very amiable waiters.

Met up with my friend for dinner and talked her in to Joe's because the one I used to go to in Oceanside, CA was great! 
 Well we sat and waited for a table for 40 minutes on a Wednesday night. The place wasn't even that packed. I promised her the food was good from what I remembered. 
Once we were seated the server greeted us in a timely matter and took our orders. She was very polite & friendly. The food took a little longer to come out than we would have liked but we were chatting anyways. We both ordered the surf and turf burgers which were a little over done but good enough. However, It was what I expected from a chain restaurant. 
All in all an ok experience. I'm sure they are just going through growing pains.

I found this nail salon to be very clean and the service was very good.  They even gave me a head massage with my brow wax!  The only thing that kept it from 5 stars was that my polish didn't last as long as my regular place and the wax didn't agree well with my skin.  I would go back if I was in the neighborhood.  My sister in law and mother LOVE this place though!

Well I had the taro. I believe the tea is suppose to be milk based...here it is powder based. If you wanted creamy you are not going to get it here. But if you like tea this may do for you. Tasted like kiks cereal without the sugar to me.

The pizza and wings are amazing!!! $10.99 for a large specialty pizza! I ordered a combo for the big game and it was beautiful! Red onion, green pepper, black olives and a crazy amount of cheese, sausage and pepperoni! Extra hot wings were great! It's like a hot buffalo sauce, not too hot and $7.99 for 10 is a deal! It's on the favorite list for sure!

We have been here a few times now and really like it. It's not perfect here but bottom line is the food is good If you need a cheesesteak, burger, or wings fix this is your spot. They also have a good beer selection. 

Service here can be hit or miss but hasn't been bad yet just seems like sometimes you get lost in the shuffle if they are busy. The first time we came here our server and service was awesome. The last two times we went it was pretty busy and food was a little slow to come out and check slow to come as well. I don't want to nit pick this was only an issue for us the last time because we had somewhere to be, and gave a credit card with check and waited like 10-15 mins before getting the check back. I didn't really mind though cause everyone was working hard they just seemed a little understaffed.

There are plenty of TV's here with with sports on. It also seems like there is always an open Mic or band in here performing which we have enjoyed.

This is a fun bar with good food, and good beer and a couple service kinks to work out, but we are fans of Creekside.

Consistently delicious panini, yummy espresso, fresh ingredients, Caffe Milano is a winner!

Open Monday-Friday for breakfast and lunch (though I've only had the opportunity to enjoy lunch there).  The owner and chef moved to Tucson from Italy a few years back and brought their delicious food culture with them.  

The panini are fabulous - always crispy on the outside but not-too-crispy on the inside and filled with fresh, delicious ingredients.  A great place to check out if you are in downtown for lunch.
Literally beyond amazing! The food is delicious. The service is superb, and the portions are sizable for the fine cuisine I'm a well traveled foodie from NYC and I would highly recommend this place!

Delivery tonight from skip the dishes. The shrimp egg roll and shrimp with snow peas was really good. The steamed dumplings were awful, extremely thick and tough dough. I picked the meat out and threw away the dumpling. Dont order them!!!

Consistency is the greatest virtue of Ole. Food is Tex-Mex, sort of uninteresting, but not bad. It's just not inspired. The service is above average, although one time I did have a waiter who would only speak directly to the men in the group, so that was weird. Generally, the servers are efficient and professional and take their jobs seriously. It can get really crowded in here because it's the kind of Mexican food Americans really love - non-threatening! Great for families with kids, because the food is kind of bland, but colorful. Cheese crisp is pretty good, so are the veggie tacos. They also have whole beans as well as refried, which is nice. The guacamole is fresh, and pretty good. This is a fairly loud restaurant, so if you like a party vibe, it's for you. Reminds me a little bit of Guadalajara Grill, on a smaller scale without the tableside salsa shtick.

Thanks to Noord for a great dinner on Thursday night.  For appetizers, the seared scallop was fantastic and the salmon special (fritters) were lighter than expected and delicous.  For entrees, the stuffed trout was very tasty and cooked perfectly; I loved the sauce and the greens it was served with.  The roasted seasonal vegetables were beautiful and the dressing on the salad they were served with provided some nice bite.  Loved the almond cake we had for dessert.  I'll definitely be back!

Nice, clean Laundromat. Recently (one month ago) replaced all the washers and dryers with new models. Prices were raised to 2.00$ per wash or dry cycle. 

I have run into some crowds here in the afternoon, waiting for dryers can take a while sometimes. 

I only come here because of the location, but it does happen to be one of the nicer places. They also claim they will start accepting credit cards soon.
I've been to Arby's before but my first time at this location. Service was good on this day and it's a clean facility.

My favorite lunch buffet in all of STL and that's saying something. I love Indian food and India's Rasoi is so good- even at a buffet lunch which is usually when other places put out there flavorless, boring stuff, with a few good dishes to keep people coming back. India's Rasoi puts the stars of their menu on the buffet everyday and it's really reasonably priced at under $10 per person. I love the aloo gobi and the chicken tikka lal mirch. Rasoi offers dinner as well, but the prices are higher and the food is the same as the lunch buffet. Oh, and this place caters events as well. I went to a wedding recently who had Rasoi cater it and it was the best! People wouldn't stop raving about the food!

Krause Key has never let me down. When no one else could make a copy of my front door key, they were able to make it. When I was evicting a tenant, the sheriff was late, but the key technician was very patient. I can't thank them enough.
Really great food, wonderful martini,  and friendly service. Came when in Boise to visit family and enjoyed the downtown vibe.

Great for social gatherings. They have private rooms, tables to accommodate large parties, an expansive patio, and a lively bar. The restaurant is beautifully designed and decorated down to every detail including the restrooms. 

Service has never disappointed. Staff is always friendly and never forgetful. I prefer to come here for drinks and appetizers over entrées. I'm not a fan of the burnt crust on the pizzas, I haven't found one menu item I really enjoy, the hollandaise sauce from brunch had great flavor but the thick gelatinous consistency was a turn off, and their $16 Ceasar salad came with only three shrimp -  bringing me to the conclusion that apps and drinks are the way to enjoy Ava for me. 

The location, the gorgeous dining room, people watching on the patio, and the friendly atmosphere are what keeps me coming back.
Phenomenal place with a great menu! Affordabe prices too, especially when you take into account the portion sizes. Highly recommend it to anyone even if you aren't familiar with middle eastern food.

Very nice car wash. The fact that it's conveniently located next to my apartment complex is nice too. The conveyor belt design is nicer than the normal track design that are other car washes. It does a good job getting the car clean still find small areas of left on dirt. The materials for the brushes and scrubbers seems better than other car washes I've been too. The free vacuum is fantastic has plenty of suction and the tips have the nice small pointed ends, to get in sides and hard spots of your vehicle. Overall pretty good car wash for the money.

I had a terrible fall last month and Dr. Walker performed emergency surgery on me the very next morning. I was concerned since it was a difficult surgery including two titanium rods being placed to hold my femur (long bone) in place for healing, they will remain permanently. 

I will be setting off the X-ray machines off at the airports ;) 

It's amazing how youthful Dr. Walker looks for someone with such accomplishments. He did his residency at the Minnesota Mayo Clinic! That's impressive. He was very kind and caring, addressing all my questions and concerns. I was a little surprised when I saw my X-ray the first time...I was surprised at the sheer size of those titanium rods. It's pretty shocking how large they are; one is from hip to knee and the other is from hip to other rod at top.

I had my first post-on appointment at ROC and I was pretty impressed with the facility even though it's 50 years old. There is a whole area for physical therapy and rehabilitation. This place is a well oiled machine and I hardly had to wait at all for my appointment. 

Dr. Walker is a excellent physician and did a Epic surgery on me, after only 4 weeks I am walking well, and barely need to use my cane. Wow after reading others reviews I feel blessed that I ended up with D. Walker as my surgeon. 

5 stars!!

Switched from Frontier to Spectrum (Bright House) in April, but returned to Frontier again because the internet connection would often fail. An inside and outside technician came out, then the service was out for the entire neighborhood and after it came back on briefly it was out again and another technician wondered why all of the equipment hadn't been replaced.  I had service for a week before the same issues started again.  Switched back to Frontier but their customer service is just as bad.  Looking at other options.  Neither have earned my loyalty.
I love this salon. I have curly hair and Liz always does an amazing job at blow drying my hair without the need of a straightener. I had virgin hair until I let her give me a balayage  and I love it!

Definitely not the best Chinese food  that I've ever had, but it is also far from the worst.  The service is good, the restaurant tends to be kept clean, and for the price, it is probably some of the better that you can get.  If you are willing to spend more money for quality, I'd recommend Two Guys From Hong Kong, but for the price, it sure is better than pretty much anyone else who charges the same amount.
Been coming here for 10 years+ never had a cover charge to watch a fight. It's only a 2 star because the wings are still good.

Let's have an honest chat about the meat to bean ratio.

My wife and I went to this Wendy's last week. I ordered the chili. When I order chili I expect it to have at least a tangible amount of meat in that thing. I don't care if it's cat meat, emu, human, just focking put some meat in that thing. Instead, I get this cup of goo that's so full of beans and no meat that it reminds me of my days in elementary chugging Elmer's glue by the liters. And I mean this chili was gross; It looked like cow cum mixed with chili seasoning and brought to room temperature. Just for me. I could take a shite that looked more like a chili. The aliens would agree cuz they probed me last week, so they'd know for sure, but I'm tellin' ya: Where's the meats. Apparently this product needs a label on the side of the chili cup that says "Must provide your own meat. Meat not included". C'mon, Wendy, are you too lit up on bong water to give us at least some possum in that chili of yours? Are you too drunk stumbling around fighting gravity, twerking to Lady Gaga, to at least throw some meat flavor into this chili. Excuse me, I mean "chili". This stuff's more suitable for brick mortar. I think if I eat this, my butt cheeks are gonna get glued shut as I'm trying to take a chris later after eating it. Wendy, even the United Nations would call this chili crimes against humanity. Next time, and I don't care who you throw into the pot, stick some god damn meat in this thing.

This review isn't about the food because we all know five guys is delicious. This review about the customer service which was lacking in all ways. I am a time restricted person so if I order online and it gives me a time to pick my food up, well that's exactly what I want. I shouldn't come in to find that you're still preparing my order (and I was a few minutes late arriving). Additionally the fact that you couldn't remember my simple burger during 3pm non rush hour is ridiculous. I won't be at this five guys ever again!

Awesome little spot on Harbor Island! The valet at the Westin recommended this spot to us as his favorite for fish tacos. Great service, fresh food, great location. We had the the fried green tomatoes, mac and cheese, and scallops. All were delish. Definitely get the side of mac and cheese no matter what - it did not disappoint! I didn't get a photo as I devoured it immediately - oops.  The menu is seasonal. Highly recommend!

Absolutely phenomenal. We had the french toast, the three little pigs sandwich and an order of biscuits and gravy to top it off. Everything was delicious, but the biscuits and gravy were pretty much a religious experience. Waited an hour to get in for brunch on a Sunday and would do it again in a heartbeat.

Let me be clear first- I am a fan of Chef Stern's food. 

I have waited many months for Centro to open and to have his food once again. So on opening night a table of 16 show up at prime time to try this new spot out. Centro is small plate style food. Plates that are intended for sharing and enjoying with a drink and friends. The plates range from $2 - 8 include Brussels sprouts, tacos, pumpkin bisque , roasted beets and many other delicious dishes. Large plates $12-16 included bone marrow and ribeye.  The popcorn was addictive with flavors that had tang, salt and sweet. We couldn't put our finger on it but you just kept eating it. I enjoyed the marrow with garlic chips that had a hint of sweet yet a nice crunch. The ribeye was tender and well seasoned. And of course I love brussel sprouts so it was hard to share them. Also with kitchen right there and food brought to the table when it's ready- everything was piping hot. You could see the steam whisper off the ribeye. 

Ryan our waiter was really put to the test. 8 separate checks, drink orders, and food orders that must have been about 23 plates. Since the plates are meant to be shared they don't all come out at once, and he had a lot of running to do.  He really tried to balance the separate checks and the new pos system, thank you, it had to be hard. 

The interior was beautiful. Bare red brick wall and hard wood floors. Full open kitchen, and you know I always suggest sitting where you can enjoy watching the chef cook. Our group was too big so next time I have my bar spot picked out to watch Stern in action. 

My mistake for not looking at the beer, wine and drink menu better, but we had just came from happy hour. 

I can't wait for summer to come so I can hang out on the back patio

I can't recommend German Motorworks enough... the service is just superb--reasonable, efficient and thorough. My 525i needed a ton of work, and Bret prioritized, talked me through the issues, provided a very fair estimate and completed the work in no time. If you're in Nashville or surrounding areas and looking for a go-to for your BMW, this is your place.

Easily accessible off 40W.

Terrifying! Great actors and props.  They put a lot of time and thought into everything.  Even while in line you could get spooked!  I highly recommend that you purchase your tickets online and arrive right at opening -- we did not wait in line.

This restaurant is a hidden gem. With more than a few Italian restaurants vying for the title of best in Reno, Un Caffe' is the real deal; Elegant, cozy interior, wonderful live music the night I was there, a guitarist who thankfully played flamenco only occasionally- does every place have to play flamenco every night? I love variety, and to hear acoustic Santana was great.
The food. I started with a Caprese' Salad, perfectly done with thick slabs of fresh mozzarella and drizzled with a gooey-black balsamic reduction that was amazing. I  ordered the prosciutto pizza, small enough for one and absolutely delicious, the best I have had since sitting in a cafe in Rome. There is a Chef in the kitchen, obviously. 
Attentive staff, decent wine list, Noise level perfect for conversation. This is a great place.

Stopped in on a recommendation from a bar tender at another local brewery we had lunch at earlier in the day.  Loved the vibe, beer selection and set up.  You can easily relax here all day.  The covered patio outside was spacious and comfortable.  They had Corn hole, connect four and Jenga to keep the kids (little and big) occupied.  A Thai and Sushi food truck was also parked out front for folks that want  some noms with their beer.  I really enjoyed listening to the live music as well.  So glad we took the advice and checked this spot out.  We will be back and we will bring friends.

This place is just adorable!!! We loved the food, and there was amazing service! Very friendly staff, quick service. Tacos were amazing!!! I'd say if anything, less ice in the pitchers of margaritas.  For a whole pitcher, we only got 2 drinks out of it.  Otherwise, happy customers. Thanks!

Very knowledgeable and professional employees and one of the best Vape Shops in the New Orleans area hands down! Very good house juices to choose from and to top it off a nice place to hang out And Vape with some friends!
The sweetest staff! The coffee is amazing and love there gluten free muffin selection. I think I've tried all of them. Love the kid magnet board in the back, great for my daughter to play!

Another five star outing at Evangeline"s Bistro and another night of five star food and service.  We came here for an early dinner and the place was filling up quickly.  Remember they have valet parking but a little farther down the street is a paid parking lot.  We sat at the bar with our cocktails (a French 75 for me) and looked over the menu.  There were no specials that evening.  

We shared the shrimp remoulade.  Large shrimp served over a bed of romaine leaves with home made remoulade sauce.  The shrimp were delicious but I especially loved the remoulade sauce with the lettuce leaves.  It was so tasty and crisp and fresh.   For our main meal, Majordomo went with the blue crab etouffee.  It looked delicious and the next time I looked over, it was gone.  I went with the duck balsamique.  A large portion of duck that was served with roasted potatoes and sautéed spinach with garlic and ginger.  "Try it, you'll like it."

Would I come back here?  You know I will.

I stopped in while visiting this weekend for a work trip with my colleague. We had an absolutely wonderful experience. The atmosphere is stunning, but more importantly the food, service, and drinks were outstanding. I ordered the shrimp and grits, my coworker ordered the wild boar on special. Both of us were silent for the entire (very short) duration that we inhaled our meals. The main word I would use to describe my meal is balanced; zest, zing, sweet & savory all at the same time. My coworker was shocked that they were able to make wild boar taste like a filet mignon. Totally amazing, huge thanks to our server Brandon for making our experience even more exceptional. 

Note: this is the best priced upscale restaurant in Indianapolis. If you haven't been, definitely visit and bring all of your friends. The food is

Does the world need a 537th review of Fido? Absolutely not. But I'm hoping the Fido people will read my comments and take action, and I will have improved the world. 

I went to Fido on a weekday morning to purchase and consume a cappuccino, and I had to wait approximately 15 minutes in line behind multiple breakfast orderers. This is much longer than my preferred wait time. I believe the standard solution to this problem is to have a separate line for coffee-only orders. When there's no one in the coffee-only line, the counterperson can take someone from the other line. I didn't think this up myself; I have seen it in action at coffee shops around the globe. 

Fido, won't you help me improve the world by instituting this change?

The cappuccino, BTW, was very good. Hence four stars.

Great servers, all online ordering. Great place for birthday celebration. VERY loud music. Food and drinks came quickly. They checked on us a lot. Nice to park in the free garage around the corner. Vegan options.

This was on my list for a while to go and try. Rated 19th in the country for BBQ and featured on Food Network. 

We got there around 7 and had about a 50 minute wait which is what I expected when I saw how small the place was. Because it was so small, it felt cramped and loud, but it had a good atmosphere overall. 

The server was really nice and went over the menu and pointed out the most popular items for us. For me and my friend's appetizer, we got the corn bread, and it was incredible. It was moist, had a crisp outside, and was buttery and delectable.  

For our meals, we decided to get 2 different entrées and split them! My friend got the bratwurst burger with fries, and I got the B.O.S.S. burger with the Mac N' Cheese. My friends was incredible, juicy and flavorful. Mine was nothing like that to be honest. It was dry, and the cheese sauce just added to the dryness. I had to use the bottles of BBQ sauce to get it down even with the cheese sauce. 

Overall, service was a 5, atmosphere was a 4, and food was a 4. I can't really say I'm gonna rush back, but I still recommend that you try it.
Very good BBQ  great wings  price wasn't to bad and good sized portion great feel to the place   Def suggest this place
worst office ever.. No calls returned for days or weeks. You could literally die waiting.. Or end up with many ER visits.  They have been blaming the phone system problems for years..
