Sadly I have to say my last Puckett's experience at this location was nowhere nearly as nice as my last one in Franklin.  I really have enjoyed the Franklin location and I had thought that I would most certainly enjoy this location but that was not the case.  I was disappointed they were out of the special of the day even though I arrived shortly after they opened as somehow "it didn't get made or something" according to my server.  So I rolled with the punches and decided to try the burger instead.  The food took a really long time to come out and the server kept coming back apologizing for the wait.  I started to get a bit nervous about the wait time as I had an important meeting coming up so my time was growing thin but finally my food arrived.  Unfortunately my order ended up being a less than good burger as it was too much on the burned crispy side.  I didn't have time to send my food back so I grimly crunched through the crispy burned burger patty and went off to my meeting in a less than happy state.  I KNOW Puckett's can do much better food than this so I'm not sure what series of troubles happened to result in my poor experience on this last visit but something was surely amiss in the kitchen that day.

Today was the second time I've dined here and was very happy with the food and service. My sausage and cheese egg white omelet was cooked perfectly and was so large, I took half home. The chocolate chip pecan pancakes were delicious! The crepes are another delicacy; we ordered them to go. Quite crowded, but it's bc the food is good and it's on the Main Line. Only reason I didn't give 5 stars is bc they charge $2.00 extra for egg whites which I feel is a little excessive
Always great service, amazing spring rolls, and delicious pho.  I've eaten here at least 50 times and have never been disappointed.

It's nice to find quality ethnic food in the suburbs of Indy.This definitely fits that description. My wife ordered a bunch of stuff the first time for take out. I fell in love with their curry. 
All of their food traveled well for take out.

Since then, I've gone in for lunch twice... Soup, spring roll and an entree for $7? Can't beat that. I've had all three currys... The red and yellow with chicken were excellent! Plus it comes with a nice sized ball of rice.
This has quickly become a favorite spot for me.
Very clean interior and restrooms.  Food quite good but the omelettes needed some extra seasoning.  Would definitely recommend to others and would visit again.

I don't often write reviews of businesses, but I have to say that dealing with Philadelphia Auto Body has been a great experience.  They deserve to have a shout out.  Their shop is clean, the staff is extremely courteous, and their work is meticulous.   After I was rear-ended at the airport, these guys have taken care of every detail of dealing with the insurance company and getting my car back in shape.  It's not often you hear  praise for auto shops, but this place really deserves its great reputation.

I have been coming to palace diner since I was about 7 years old. Every time I have gone I've  always had great service and a great meal. But the other night was different. We had a very rude waitress. She had a very sarcastic tone and forgot multiple things. When another person I was with asked if they could have an extra plate Donna asked "what do you need the plate for" in a very condescending tone. You never question the customer like. She just had a very rude tone. I don't expect exceptional service from a diner but being sarcastic and rude is out of line.

I never ever really leave reviews, but the service here was so poor, I had too... First impression was it wasn't to bad, but then I tried to order, I was literally the only customer in the building, but it took forever to get somebody's attention, when I did, I still had to wait to order, while ordering the cashier couldn't hear me over the loud Spanish music, I had to repeat it many times, prolly why they didn't get it right. When my food was done, the cashier yelled at me from across the restaurant, "AYE! YOUR ORDER IS READY!", gave me 2 plates when there was clearly 3 of us, gave me attitude when I asked for a 3rd, while eating, I noticed the salad bar was filthy, the restaurant appeared to be fully staffed but everyone was either sitting around wasting time or watching the T.V. restaurant was FILTHY...1 STAR... EARNED... pizza was really good, even if it wasn't what I ordered...

Decided to try the ribs.  Ugh. Gross. Burgers came out burned but tastey (to be fair, we did ask for well done) cheddar cheese is smoked too. My fault, I should've asked. But to me. It's pretty bad. Easy to remove since it's not melted anyway.  To recap:
Ribs - Horrible
French Fries - Crap

Can't believe they're in business at all.
Never, ever going back. I still have that foul taste in my mouth... Ugh

This is a newer Hampton Inn and it is absolutely gorgeous!

Hampton Inn is part of the Hilton family of hotels, therefore much is to usually be expected of them (even if they do cost less per night than let's say a Doubletree location). This location is situated near other hotel chains, across from a Hilton, and has a few surrounding restaurants. At the end of the day, it's still in a part of Delaware that requires a car to get around but it's a comfy place to crash for the night.

The lobby is modern and updated, it also comes equipped with a small store for the essentials (toothpaste, water, snacks, deodorant, etc.). There is also a seated area since breakfast is served FREE everyday from 6-10AM. The hallways are brightly lit and they have the tap card system so you no longer have to dip your room card and pray you get in. The rooms are MASSIVE. Hamptons used to be known for rooms on the smaller side but these are huge. One king-size bed, a full couch, a desk and coffee table, and a dresser that houses the Samsung TV with cable. There is also free wifi, as there is at most Hilton locations.

Breakfast was ok but hit the spot and was good since we were hitting the road fairly early. The staff was friendly and helpful with the check-in process. Everything at this location is pretty fantastic and I cannot recommend it enough if you're in the area!

I definitely recommend this place for the games and sports lounge, but I can't say the same for the food, service or drinks. 

Although it wasn't the worst service I'd ever experienced, it was far from good. The waiter brought the wrong drinks, couldn't answer questions about the menu, and even asked "do we actually have that on the menu?" when I ordered something. When my husband ordered a steak with Chimmichuri sauce, the waiter made a face and asked "you like that green stuff?"
He was just too old to be soo unprofessional, but like I said, it wasn't the worst service ever. 

The signature drinks and margaritas are terrible, so I suggest sticking to beer, wine and standard mixers (rum and coke, vodka cran, gin and tonic, etc.).

Next time I take my son for games, I'll eat at the Hibachi downstairs and then go to D&B for the games. Oh yeah, I forgot to mention, that this place tends to draw in some trashy people who (no pun intended) leave trash all around the hallway and game floor.
Great bagels! We often lament not having good local bagel places in Austin. This is a great little spot. The owner is from Boston, and he knows what he's doing! Espresso drinks are good too

Jamba I see you! Wow I was pleasantly surprised by this new addition to the menu. 
I was as delicious as it sounded! 

pb wow cacao
fat free frozen yogurt, bananas, unsweetened almondmilk, peanut butter, organic cacao powder  toppings: bananas, organic granola, strawberries, peanut butter, coconut chips, sliced almonds

One minor disappointment was the granola has cinnamon so I opted for some extra strawberries. 

Super friendly staff and clean facility!
Great food, convenient location, friendly staff and chef walks around greeting people - can't go wrong/will be back.

Excellent Service 5+ stars! 
I order often from Amazon & I am always pleased when I see that Intelcom Courrier Canada Inc. (Edmonton) are the chosen ones to deliver my order. I appreciate the realtime updates where my package is & when it's been delivered in the off chance I'm not home & just today delivered to me even on a Sunday with bad road conditions & again today delivered to me an entire day early! 
Very, Very impressed with Intelcom Courrier Canada Inc. (Edmonton)
thank you & keep up the Great work
Everyone on this Trident Mortgage team was excellent, very effiecient, and made the process of buying my first home very unstressfull.

Delicious. Good price and happy hour. All profits go to homeless..like old fashioned diner with pie case and all. Breakfast is good too. My favorite is wine in can they serve is good actually. I'll be a regular for sure. Cauliflower soup and blue plate special are my favorites
This place rocks. Delicious salads and house-made dressings!
Very disappointed!  place was empty and the food was average at best...will probably not go back.  We enjoyed being out with our friends and having a drink by the fire pit after, however!!
A great place is you are looking for a cozy place for a nice beverage and a great donut or pastry with great service.  You must try.

This is our favorite Mexican place to eat since the day it opened. 
Tonight friends of our went with us since they have moved, the service was terrible. If this was our first time we would never go back.
Waiting for our table the bartender didn't have the right size glasses for the drinks we wanted then she got the orders wrong. Ok no big deal. After waiting for our table it went downhill from here instead of up. 
Our waiter Miguel was the worse service ever to be had. 
Not only could he not understand a word of our order ( thank god our friend with us speaks great Spanish) but the order was still  wrong. We had to ask for utensils and napkins several times it took me 4 times asking to get a glass of water. Asks for more chips 5 times. 
But the fact he didn't speak much English was horrible. Our friend got out of him it was only his 3 rd day..... why would you put a new guy on one of your busiest nights???? 
The food here is always good the service is hit or miss mostly hit.
Tonight was the worst service ever.

Walked in for lunch on a Saturday, it was empty and quiet.  Located in an industrial area near Oliver brewery district,  its kind of off the beaten path.  Menu overhead the kitchen window, place your order and go sit at the big long tables with plywood tops.

There are a 4-5 options for homemade sausages to choose from and sides to go with.  I chose the spicy Hungarian with a pretzel and cheese spatzle.  

Local Alberta beers are on tap and there are some good choices.  

Food was good, spatzel was excellent, sausage was very good, pretzel was ok.  

Id certainly go again, how can you go wrong with sausage, beer and pretzels?

When I come to the STL for business I make a point to eat at Bogart's Smokehouse. Their ribs are are fall off the bone delicious and the baked beans pair well with chicharrones. I'm a California native and can say that the best BBQ is located in St. Louis.

This was a no for me. It was my first time here. I really wanted nachos and they had quite the variety. Ended up ordering the bleacher 'chos. The chips were more of a multigrain chip. The 5 cheese queso was thick and salty and the jalapeños were too salty as well. Combine that with the $12 price, I was more than disappointed. Definitely NOT anything close to traditional nachos. Maybe the quesadillas are better.

Do not come here ! Management tried to  credit the bill or give us a discount for next time but I denied it as I didn't want to make a scene and I don't plan on returning. 
The whole staff catered to a family in the restaurant who proceeded to change the babies diapers in a restaurant booth we were sitting next to. Hopefully they cleaned that booth.

The crawfish wasn't cleaned and flavor was terrible and the crawfish was bland inside. 
The salt and pepper shrimp was cooked with ALL of the shell on so of course all the seasoning was pointless as soon as it was peeled. Just laziness of the kitchen staff. 

The service was probably worse. Our waitress spoke only Chinese so it worked out we had someone with us who could order. But even in the Chinese exchange, she was difficult to deal with as she still didn't know anything and kept having to clarify EVERYTHING we ordered. There was inconsistency with the specials and pricing.

It all ended with no chocolate pudding... The story begins with five friends on a girls weekend to tour Philly and go to Comicon.  After a long, long day, standing in many lines to meet the best nerdy stars, we started looking for a place near our hotel to eat a late dinner.  When you see a place with a nearly empty parking lot on a Saturday night, it might be best to keep driving.  But it's a diner -- how bad can the food be....well turns out pretty bad.  
As my one friend reviewed all five dishes -- she summed it up perfectly.  Tastes like "food."  Personally she was stretching it a little.  Food was terrible.  Hot food was cold.  Chicken was dry.  Burgers were bland.

And then there was the service and lack of pudding.  Each meal was supposed to come with chocolate pudding, ice cream or some other dessert (don't remember).  As we ate our food -- served by our bad attitude server -- we joked about the chocolate pudding we were going to get.  When were were done, our server gave pudding to a table nearby, immediately came to our table and just handed us our checks....no chocolate pudding or any dessert offered to us.  As it was now around 9pm and we were all very tired, we decided to get just leave and drink wine in our room.

I don't know what's worse about this place --- the gross food, nasty servers, or lack of chocolate pudding.

What a great restaurant. Yes, I could say what a great Chinese restaurant, but this is simply a great restaurant. Kind staff, well run, great for Carry Out's and the food is simply delicious. If you are north of Ina Road and are looking for the Chinese niche this is the only place to go. 6 stars if I could!

Eagle Creek State Park is one of the premier recreation areas in the city. Located on the far northwest quadrant of Indy, this park offers up all kinds of activities and venues for the whole family. Billed as one of the largest municipal parks in the United States, Eagle Creek has something that many parks do not: a massive body of water on which one can sail, fish, swim or watch a rowing event

In recent years, the park has added new features and buildings including the Earth Discovery Center and the Peace Learning Center a Bark Park and more..

The land on which the park sits belonged to the Lilly family and was donated to Purdue University in the 1950s, who later sold it to the city. The city built an earthen dam in the park to control flooding and this maneuver led to the Eagle Creek Reservoir that makes up a large portion of the recreation site. 

All in all, this is a great place to take the family for a picnic, ride a bike, canoe or just about any outdoor activity. Be forewarned, though....in the summer, the park can be packed and you might find it too crowded to enjoy. This is why I have personally scouted some other parks. We tend to head to Eagle Creek during odd days and times to avoid the crush. But, one of the best times to visit is in the winter months when you can just drive around and see lots of deer and other wildlife because the trees are bare - just don't feed anybody!!

I had panzarotti's here for the first time. However, they were way to oily. They do not compare to the consistently good panzarotti's I have gotten from Sal's Pizzeria in Marlton, NJ. The place is spartan, with security windows. However the service was friendly. Not much room to eat here.

Is it based on the reviews the veggie burger. It is just a plain old black burger despite the description. Definitely not worth trying. Definitely A great ambience but other than that no reason to go.

The food is eh...but the ice cream is WOW!

with all the ice cream, how can you choose? well my suggestion is come back every weekend and tackle each flavor one-at-a-time.  By far the best is when we decide to split one of their delicious brownie sundaes.  Their prices are fair, their staff is friendly and the location is easy to get to and not to busy to just lounge outside while watching the passerbys.

More Than Just Ice Cream we will see you this weekend!

ps. forgot to mention their red velvet cupcakes pure red deliciousness.
It had to be done. I had to go on the mighty Mississippi.  One Northern Girl had her wish fulfilled here.
Muy rico todo. Estábamos en busca de camarones a la diabla y nos encontramos con La Guerrerita Mexican Restaurant. Muy amables y muy buen servicio. 100% recomendado!

Visited for our Anniversary and we loved it.  Sat outside and enjoyed the breeze and view after walking down the River walk.  Excellent menu options with really unique items, it was hard to choose.  Had the broiled oysters and gator soup to start, both were very good, would order them again.  Main entrees were steak and vegetarian plate; we both really enjoyed our meal.  An extra treat was a small box of chocolate truffles for our anniversary; a very nice touch.  Service was great and the location can't be beat.  We will go again and again and I recommend for anyone with an adventurous palate

GREAT PLACE TO EAT....Yelp nailed it on this one. Old pub atmosphere with great service. The cheesesteak egg rolls were by far the best I've ever had. We had a table of 6 and ate several different food options (Philly, Fish and Chips, Shepherds Pie, Crab Cakes and Sliders), all of which was phenomenal. Everyone left with a huge smile on their face and a full stomach. Definitely coming back next time I'm in Philly !!!!!

The only time I'll see the inside of this place again is on Kitchen Nightmares! Was craving Arby's and found it replaced by this dive. I can appreciate the uniqueness of the way it's been painted but the menu ... Well...... I'm not sure there is a menu. Nothing but black marker written on plain white paper and no prices. Very disjointed and unorganized. Even tried reading an actual menu that was on the counter and it was blurry xerox copies. To keep it short, the food was below average and overpriced. They screwed up our order. Though the service, tried to be helpful and friendly, couldn't seem to get it together very well. Even had to go back and ask for our credit card that they forgot to return. The over all impression I get is they did well at the rib cook off and turned their stand into restaurant. I will be surprised if they are still open next year.

Chose to stay center city Philadelphia for our trip and Le Meridien  served its purpose. It's a nice posh hotel. The exposed indoor brick was cool looking down into common area. The rooms were  bright w/ views of the city. Not the most comfortable bed but still slept well. 
It seems weddings our def their thing and we saw 2 wedding parties during our one night stay. 
Decided to go downstairs to the bar for a nightcap and the bartender was fantastic. Charming, attentive, and polite. However management should really consider giving the guy help during wedding events. Next thing you know a wedding party arrives and the poor guys is bombarded w/ drink requests. So unfair! One bartender and fifty people surrounding the bar. He obliged every guest w/ diligence and patience even when a fight broke out amongst the guests! It just seemed like a very hectic situation and we felt uncomfortable just watching him have to juggle all the requests (like a pro might I add). But when a hotel has guests that feel bad even asking for drinks cuz they are overworking their employees they should really consider hiring coworkers!!!!!
Also they had some questionable characters on the corner of their street around 11pm. I can only describe as some ladies of the night types w/ their managers? HAHA. Or maybe thats just how people hang these days lol. But all in all nice hotel and convenient area

I have had it with this office. For three days I have been trying to get a prescription refilled. The office staff is completely incompetent!!! I would not recommend this office to anyone. Last problem I had a doctor told me I had to see a vascular surgeon. I asked her why she told me "she couldn't tell me because she didn't want to step on the doctor toes who ordered the test. After several phone calls to the doctor who ordered the test no response , I called and said"I am coming to the office and will sit in the waiting room until someone talks to me!! Finally I got some answers, but that is I had to resort to. I told them tonight, that I will be in the office at 8:30 tomorrow and will not leave until I get my prescription. Terrible staff!! Very rude and incompetent

I'm a fan. I love this place. I overeat every time I visit but it's totally worth it. Dimsum on the weekend for lunch is a great option.

The service at times could be a little off but the food is great (especially for the price).
I go at least once a week.  It's kind of an addiction.  Best hot chicken and turnip greens!
This is a nice place to come do work and get a beer. The food is just alright for the price but is nice to have when you're working for a while in the yard.

If you're looking for sultry place to have a great drink, this place will satisfy your alchy taste buds for sure. I wish there were more small bars like this back in SoCal!

AMBIANCE - 5 STARS
I immediately liked the ambiance upon stepping into the bar via a secret back hallway that adjoins the restaurant 47 Scott next door, which was super convenient because it was rainy outside! When we arrived for a bday dinner next door and were told there was a wait, someone came up with a genius idea to sneak next door for a drink while we were waiting for the table. There was plenty of seating when we arrived around 8 pm and we chose a cozy little booth on the side. 

SERVICE-  5 STARS
The bartender was super knowledgable about his craft and made some helpful recommendations. My drink tasted exactly as he described! Perfection! He also had separate checks ready for us very quickly.

DRINKS - 4 STARS
The drink names are so fun! My drink I think, was called the Northern Negotiator, which had apple Jack and a hint of balsamic reduction. It was slightly salty, sweet and strong, and kind of weird, just how he had described! I liked it. My girlfriends also ordered drinks with some fun names..I think taste-wise I really liked the Bidi Bidi Bom Bom, I might order that one next time. They're all so fun and different & I'm sure there's something for everyone. 
The only bad thing is that the drinks are kind of pricy --- BUT they are strong. These are definitely hand-made specialty drinks, not your club drinks that are just thrown together with splurts of vidka and soda flying everywhere. If you want to get your drink on hard core, you might go broke; but for a pre-dinner drink a few people or a late night rendezvous, it's perfect :)

PS - icing on the cake? Latin/salsa music playing in the background! :))))))
Great beer selection! Friendly wait staff. Best wings ever. Delish pizza. You can NOT go wrong!

The food was great but our service was terrible. Our server wasn't aware of the drink specials so my friend who got hot chicken was suppose to get free beer but wasn't aware and also was charged more for her drink when she asked the server prior to ordering it. I ordered a pulled pork sandwich but needed a plate since it was served in a basket so I had to wait 15 minutes for a server to come and then I finally asked another sever who brought me one 10 minutes. My food got cold but I was so hungry, I just had to eat it. The band that was playing was amazing and overall a decent experience my best suggestion is to have more than 3 servers on the floor on a Saturday night. Pictures are our tenders with Mac and cheese, hot chicken and a pulled pork sandwich. I would say 3.5 stars but the food was really good.

Had a very pleasant time here thanks to my friendly waitress. I came here at around 9PM on June 9, 2018. 

Ordered a steak and the South American fish. Both were absolutely delicious and portions were solid. Each item on the menu has a calorie count, which is a huge plus to me!

Will be returning.

I come here at least once a year when I visit family in the area. It's their favorite place, and I don't mind it. My grandfather enjoys the all you can eat steak, and I enjoy the variety of chicken. Fried, rotisserie, bourbon and a handful of other ways. I will say in a party of six, two of the people got sick, presumably from bourbon chicken, but no one is really sure. I have an iron stomach so... it's a moot point to talk about that. If you're hungry, and can get the senior discount, I would say that it's worth a stop in.

Was pretty good ordered shrimp garlic pasta wasn't anything to holler about.. they do give u bread & butter to start u off which is a plus.. the butter should be room temp tho so its easier to spread on not warm bread.. the best part imo is the dessert which u have to order w/ur meal bc its made to order. I had the apple pie OMG so damn good ill just eat the crust w/out the apples in it very fresh & good will definitely be back bc the fresh dessert is a must
It seems to be a popular one but it was just okay nothing to write home about and I definitely wouldn't go again. ‍
A well priced and very large portion chirashi sushi bowel.  The decor is clean and nice.  Although it is a typical main-line restaurant it is good quality for the $$ price and service is friendly.
Consistently good food services wonderful bar Services great and the drinks taste good. Beef dip is one of the best I've eaten that comes on a fresh-baked baguette

I'm excited to see another coffee shop (re)-surface in the central downtown area and with my condo a year away from completion, *fingers crossed*, I can only welcome new businesses and restaurants to the 104 St area with anything but livid excitement. Last week I had a rare weekday off, finally getting a chance to check out Transcend Mercer, which opened its doors last Monday.

Transcend is not new to the Edmonton scene, the Transcend Mercer being their third to join its Argyl and Garneau locations, but a fourth venture, after the closing of their Jasper Ave location last year. I had just discovered the Jasper location as a prime spot for relaxing and blogging when they announced their closure, unable to sustain their coffee-centric philosophy in a large downtown space. The Mercer location is now only four blocks away from the downtown core of Jasper Avenue, much smaller, although definitely a coffee-focused shop. I was excited to see if I could set up shop there! Future photo-editing and blogging space? Sorry Credo, you're closer but my God why are you always so busy, sad face.

Parking is almost near impossible in downtown and even more with the construction of the Rogers arena just north of the site. A lot of the clientele, I assume, are from businesses around the area or people who live in the downtown core and, of course, MacEwan University students looking for their caffeine-fix. The newly opened space is in the basement of Mercer Warehouse, down the stairs, on your left. It's quite a spacious set up despite it being smaller than their Jasper Avenue location. A large wood communal table draws most of your focus, great for large groups and study area and eight smaller tables surround the perimeter for those who want a more intimate conversation or a quiet space to work. The chairs are soft leather mixed with an industrial metal frame, which I found to be stylish and comfortable. But the best seats in the house? Bar stools at the extended counter, closest to the prep counter. Best way to know your coffee barista for sure.

That day I ordered a chai latte. Something about freshly brewed coffee makes my heart palpitate despite years of coffee consumption in my University days. I must be getting old. I don't actually recall ever trying anything but their coffees at past locations because clearly I would have remembered this chai latte! Predominantly cinnamon spiced (vs. cardamom spiced), I appreciated the coffee art in my to-stay cup. WiFi is locked, but is available for free with purchase. I actually stayed there for a couple of hours though, relaxing and finishing up some blog posts. Success! I've found a local coffee shop close to my (future) home!

Welcome back downtown Transcend! Great space, great coffee, great atmosphere. Also helps that it's open on Saturdays too. Please don't leave before I move.

The gym itself is great, but as mentioned here, they outsource all of their billing to "ABC Financial." When speaking with Sweat, I made sure to get a month-to-month membership. Well, they went ahead and signed me up for an auto-renewing 1-year membership.

So boy was I surprised when I moved and was told I had to submit proof that I moved. Then 30 days later they would cancel my membership and, oh by the way, slap me with a $100+ fee.  How can I submit proof I've moved before I move? This forced me to pay for a month of the gym when I didnt even live in Philly.

I don't understand how a "local" business like Sweat can just outsource one of the most important aspects of their business to a faceless company who refuses to work with you and has no knowledge of any conversation you had with the Sweat rep. Terrible.

If you love country music, patriotism, and good beer for a decent price, this is your place. The place was packed, so it took like 10 minutes to get a beer, which I wasn't a fan of. They need a few more bartenders here, as they seem overworked. However, the bartenders made up for it with their awesome personalities and attentiveness. This place is ridiculously huge, with three floors. I stayed on the first floor most of the time. The band was absolutely amazing, playing a mixture of old and new country. They even did a few songs for the Vets that were in the bar, and it was really heartfelt. This was one of my favorite visited bars while in Nashville.
Heading out of town? Come 30 mins earlier and have breakfast first! Always speedy service, and never too crowded. Best airport food. Super fresh fruit.

Great food. I got the brie & mushroom baguettes which were entree sized even though listed as an app - sooo glad I did! Everyone in my party (of 7) thoroughly enjoyed their meals. Good service. $15 mimosas during brunch. Nice decor inside. Patio outside when it's nice out. What more can you ask for?

Here's my rundown. 
It's VERY busy. 
Monday's are one of the busiest mornings because tourists hit it up on their way to the airport. 
Still, the line moves fast and you get a menu while you're waiting so you're all set to order when you get in. 

Here's what we ate;

Bonuts - a little dry but good toppings. I'd skip it and get the Lily instead. 

East Nasty - the chicken was very flavorful but we thought it had an egg and it just didn't seem very breakfasty. Also we didn't love the biscuit 

French omelet - okay, needs more cheese 

Lily - THE BEST!!!! Honestly I'd come back just for this! Every part was great and I highly recommend it!

Do you like to wait?  If so, definitely come here.  Do you like pain?  If so, this is your spot.

I was referred to Dr. Bleiler from my dentist to get my wisdom teeth out.  I made my appointment on a Friday afternoon, hoping that most people would be working.  Unfortunately, I was wrong.  It was crowded even though I came in 20 mins early.  I waited...and waited..and waited.  Two whole hours after my scheduled appointment time.  After my procedure, I was moved to a different room while I was waking from the IV sedation.  

The aftermath was horrible.  So much pain and the pain killers were not working (but I guess that's not really the doctor's fault).  A week passed without improvement on the pain so I called the office.  The receptionist was really nonchalant about my telling her about my pain.  Eventually they told me to come in for a check-up (I was more afraid of infection than the pain).  Again I came in and there was a crowded waiting room.  They put in some medicated packing to help the shooting pain.  Boy, avoid this packing at all cost.  The most pain you can imagine as they shove some gauze-like material into your fresh gum wounds.

A few days later, I had to come back in for them to remove the packing.  Again, a lot of people were waiting (some for three hours).  Fortunately, I was quickly called back since I was just a follow-up.  The packing was taken out by the nurse but she told me that the doctor wanted to check things out as well.  So I waited...and waited...a whole hour for Dr. Bleiler to take a ten second peek into my mouth.  So disappointing..but good thing I wont have to come back again!

I just moved to the area and have been here five times in two weeks.  The gyros are great and the fries are always fresh and hot.  

As someone stated previously they don't douse the gyro in tzatziki, but they don't need to.  The gyro meat is well seasoned and tasty.  

The service has always been great.  Enough so that I had to complement the manager on his hiring,  

I can't speak about the quality at other locations but the food and service here have been top notch.

No complaints.   Highly recommended.

Came here for a car wash and a deep clean inside. Got home, opened my trunk and realized that there was still tons of dirt in there. They didn't wipe the insides of my doors, left trash in some of the doors etc. it looked horrible. Waste of money. I called the same day and left a message and no one has called back.. Save your money.

This place is fantastic.  Went for anniversary dinner.  Made reservations thru yelp and noted it was our anniversary- they gave us a window table for 2.  The place was full but great for easy conversation and the tables were spaced nicely.   Started with Loch Duart Salmon & Grilled Asparagus Salad and it was refreshing.  Had 2 glasses of their cheapest cabernet and it was mellow, perfect for my wife's barramundi and my seafood cioppino. The dishes had excellent taste and presentation. Just enough to leave you satisfied.  They gave us a complementary dessert of 5 mini carrot cupcakes - so good!  Our waiter, Phil was attentive but not overbearing. The pace of service was perfect.  We willdefinitely be back. Well done to the entire staff and owners.

I'm bucking the trend here.  I'm just not seeing what everyone else is.

I stopped in here after running an errand on lunch.  Everyone in my office said "ooh ooh go to Pei Wei it's delicious!"  Why would I not want to go?

I looked over the menu and it was reasonably priced.  I opted for the korean style tofu and veggies.  Mistake.

That tofu tasted like no tofu I've had before.  Bland and lifeless.  What was with the dark brown / nearly black outside portion?  It certainly wasn't smoked.

The veggies were pretty raw.  Not sure if they serve them that way or they were in a rush.  I like them to be somewhat cooked.

The sauce tasted like basically nothing.  Korean?  Not close.

My stomach kind of hurts to boot and I had to take tums.  I won't be returning to this place.

This boutique is owned by the one and only Reese Witherspoon. It has mid priced dresses, clothing and shoes, southern style accessories along with housewares. It's known for the Y'all tote bags and other southern expressions. They serve sweet tea as you shop. It even has lounge chairs for the boyfriends and husbands to hang while the ladies browse. Great little neighborhood with lots of local shops and restaurants.

It's a build your own poke bowl. Topping selection is great. You can get 2 different meats, and they have a large amount of sauces. Ingredients taste fresh and for those that can't make up their minds, they have recommendations

Went here today and have to say I enjoyed myself. The place is incredibly tiny, but it does have that relaxing feel. The woman behind the counter was sweet and friendly I felt. I ordered a curry lentil soup and it was delicious! I also got another piece of bread due to the cute being too small, so big ups to that! I will definitely return if I am in the mood for a good bowl of soup.

Recently moved here from NYC, and finally I found a spot that reminds me of NYC! Although in NY, they would use real candles on the table, than these fake light things. They should really use real candles. Much better ambiance. Other than that, the drinks were really good, food excellent, and servers fun. Had a great time, and I'll be back!

I have yet to receive test results two months later for my annual pap and they also tried to charge me twice for my appointment.  They also didn't send my birth control prescription to the pharmacy either so I had to wait a month to start taking them. I asked them to just hand me the prescription instead of calling them. They seem very disorganized and incompetent. The nurse practitioner was very nice though and gentle.

The first time I saw this hotel I was staying at the Hyatt and walked by admiring the building and chandlers, so I had to turn back and go in for a quick look. It was love at first sight. I thought this one of those places where if you have to ask how much it is to stay here, you can't afford it. It was only for the rich and famous.

Fast forward a few years and friends suggested we get a more "Nola" hotel than one of the big box places and booked us here. I was so excited to pull up and see it was my dream hotel, and we could afford it!!! Felt a little like a Roaring 20's starlet when the doorman in his top hat welcomed us. Room was everything I could hope for, beautifully decorated, and the bar. OMG...the bar. It's from the Grand Hotel in Paris and worth stopping in just to gaze at. And ask if Pamela is there....she will make you the best hurricane you ever had. Nothing like what you get in the quarter.

You'll recognize the rooftop pool because it's featured in so many movies. My favorite time in the pool is after dinner. You can star gaze and feel like you're in you very own pool cause no one else has caught on this is the bomb. And you work off you dinner...win win right!

We've stayed here many times, and never had a problem of any kind. The only reason we moved on was because we got free room at Harrahs and discovered how entertaining the river traffic was. That, and it does take a little longer and a little more wear and tear on our feet to get to our favorite haunts. But I highly recommend this hotel, and we still always drop by at least for a drink. The food in their Crystal Room is fab as well...we had the best Easter brunch of our life there.

I laugh at all the cheering for the Peanut Butter and Jelly at 10 p.m. First of all, who's in by 10 p.m.? Usually not us. And we're usually full and/or drunk but the one time I made a point of it and went down the table was swarmed. Free food...it was K Mart blue light special moment. One man even filled a huge thermos with the Hot Chocolate, leaving none for the rest of us in line. Same with the food...I supposed I could have waited and they would have brought more but I'd seen enough for one night. Totally not worth it. If I wanted it that bad I'd have ordered room service. lol.

Hands down the best Mexican food in the Manayunk area by a mile. The food is super fresh and very authentic. I can't wait to come back here and bring my friends. I ordered the black bean soup and the chicken enchiladas with the mole sauce.

Walked in here once at night, looked at the menu, was more expensive than we thought, considering the adorable roadside exterior.  We left, promising a return when our pockets were more full.

That was until I was notified of a 10 dollar buffet lunch Monday through Friday.  BUFFET.  Ok.  

Everything was delicious, and it was a buffet, and buffets make people (me) happy.  Creole shrimp salad, fresh greens with the best bleu cheese dressing I could imagine, and SMOKED GOUDA (god of sandwich cheese).  

The setting couldn't be more lovely, and they gave us free dessert because they thought the service they gave us was lousy.  It was not. 

FREE PECAN AND SWEET POTATO PIE.  Oh my.  

Going back this Friday for catfish and will be in for dinner next time I'm feeling special.  I wish I could be a regular.
Delicious! It is the Best buy on Rittenhouse Square, great happy hour menu and drink specials.
Best BBQ I've ever had. Hands down. Undisputed. Knock out. Grand slam. Hole-in-one. Just be prepared to wait. Alternatively, find a nice park or a patio and get it to go.

Julia is awesome, and a true artist honestly. This is the best haircut I've ever had in my life. She gave me the Swiss-army knife of haircuts too- I've sat in front of the mirror trying to style it in a way that is unflattering, and it can't be done. Ever hear a stylist say "I'm a beautician, not a magician"? Julia is a magician.
I am a cookie fanatic. I had super high expectations going in and THEY WERE MET. So so good. The best cookie I've ever had. And I've had a lot!!!

The food was delicious, I had the honey salmon with avocado and black bean mango salsa; my husband had the chicken enchiladas. We also ordered the guacamole as an appetizer. We were there around 5:30 on a Sunday evening and the restaurant appeared to be about 1/2 full. Most of the guests were seated outside, but we chose to seat indoors. We were seated right away and chips and salsa were brought out almost immediately ( the salsa wasn't my favorite). Our waitress was ok...competent but not friendly at all (I'm not sure she smiled once...maybe it was a bad day).

The process getting into this school was fine! Anything after that was not so pleasant! Unless you live in the city, don't go here! Being a working mother of three trying to go back to school, coming from my full time job to class at 6 pm and being told that if I'm 1 minute late can result into a failing grade! I was 5 minutes late due to traffic, and struggling to find parking and was treated very unfairly by this professor, resulted me dropping the class and not returning to the school! The professor was the worst professor I have ever encountered in my three years going to college!
Nice spot. They have a variety of weird flavors of ice cream and no regular flavors. Once they provide regular flavors as well as the ones they make it'll be way better.

What was wrong? Maybe it was the mouse in the hotel restaurant.Maybe it was the air conditioner that wasn't working properly while it was 104 degree outside. Maybe it was the grasshopper I found in my room. Not sure which, but I definitely won't return.

Oh man!  Everything we had was delicious.  The biscuits were amazing and the grits were melt in your mouth. Our waiter, Kinson, was right on with all of his recommendations.  The jellies were fantastic and the mimosa was on point.  We sure wish there was a Big Bad Breakfast back home.  If so, we would go all the time.

If you want to eat here on a Saturday evening, you might want to get there early, as they do "first come, first serve". We waited in the bar area for about an hour, but with their app, we could see how long our wait was and how many tables were ahead of us. I liked that, and it seemed to make the time pass a little faster.  We also got to dream/windowshop at the delicous chocolates and desserts. Makes my mouth water just remembering how delicious they looked. 

Food- we ordered the Datchos for our splurge.... Yummy. BACON!
I was in a grilled cheese kinda mood, so it was the April in Paris for me...mmm melted brie!
My husband had the waffles and tweet; he loves waffles and chicken. Our friends both had the cedar plank shimburger. No one was disappointed. We were all so full from dinner that we could not even have dessert even if we wanted to.


Needless to say, I will be back for more!!
Great menu with vegan options, dogs friendly (outdoor sitting); great outdoor sitting but slow kitchen and this may be due to the fact there are a lot of home made products

We have only been once but will go back and soon. We had reservations for a table but were having such a great time at the bar, tasting the beer, talking to the bartender and those around us, we decided to stay at the bar. There were 3 of us and we shared several of the apps which were terrific. We are fussy about our beer (all of us are homebrewers) and enjoyed each one of the Tavern's own taps that we tried. The atmosphere cozy. I don't know how they got the smell of smoke out of the place from when it was the General Lafayette but they did. Go. Drink. Eat. Talk. Have fun.

I've been here a couple of times now like 20 since they opened.. not really by choice..  and honestly I'm sure it's a hit or miss sometimes. But this time it was a major miss. My bf has celiacs and we were specific to ask if the mushroom soup was ok.  when he starts trying it I noticed it had farro...she responded that the chefs confirmed farro isn't gluten...  they could have killed him!  We sent it back. 

We ordered only the sweet sausage and she noted it down but only half way through the meal she noticed there were two spicy and says oh yeah I know there was two spicy on there so I'll bring out the other sweet ones.... again could have hurt him....

Secondly the side of mushrooms tasted like over cooked canned mushrooms at a gross pizza shop. 
The side of rosemary potatoes taste like they were boiled then tossed in oil and quickly broiled so it was greasy mushy and burnt.. 

Service took forever 20-25 min...  the music was so loud and the cappuccino was pretty flat. 

They brought us complimentary ice cream for messing up which was the only good thing there...

Yes, the tuna crudo is terrific - wish there were a few more pistachios in the dish but overall it is a thoughtful, balanced, delicious dish. My friend's salad was huge and looked great. Three of us shared 2 pizzas - the brussels sprout pizza and the arugula with spicy tomato sauce. Both were great and light as a feather. The tomato sauce was delicious but not spicy at all. The ambiance reminded me of Tribeca in New York - high ceilings and a cool factory-like feel. I had a great cocktail - wish I could remember the name.... bourbon, egg white...sigh, oh well, it was THAT good. And the price for three people with tax and tip: $85.

I lived in Bear Canyon this past winter and I was pleased. The staff are super friendly and helpful. They always remembered me and my little pup whenever we came into the office. The grounds are well maintained, and didn't take long for maintenance to complete a request. It is nice that they have the 2 pools, because often the kids are at the larger pool, so I was able to relax and read by the smaller pool. They allow pets of all kinds there, and you would never know because there wasn't piles of poop everywhere. I know that not all residents clean up after their pups, so I was pleased to see that the grounds crews took care of that. The walls are not paper thin either, so I didn't hear anything from neighbors unless they were outside.
Decent average small gym and equipment. Very overpriced. Below average trainers. One trainer calls himself a Professor. Not sure if that's qualifiable.
Great sandwiches and friendly staff! The Cheesesteak sandwich is definitely my favorite. I would highly recommend this spot for lunch. They have so many sandwiches and salads to pick from!

I love this place. Classic feel and really nice barbers. Matthew is by far the best barber I have ever had so if you want a clean haircut request him. He's really friendly as well. The owner is super nice as well. I came in once after getting in a bike wreck from a car on the way and was pretty hurt and the owner was nice enough to take me to the break room and give me a wash cloth with ice. Best experience I've ever had at a barber shop. Always a pleasure and will be going here as long as I live downtown Indy. Check this place out, you won't be let down!

This salon is ok. I'll agree with the other posts that for the most part all of the stylist are really friendly and will make you feel comfortable. My biggest complaint is that it's a bit over priced for services. Yes I get that it's a salon in the "city" but nevertheless still a bit too much. I came in and asked for a fade, and shape up (I didn't have much hair to cut since I already had my hair pretty short), I just wanted to clean it  up a bit. I left the salon with a mediocre cut- and it cost me $65- I could have gotten the same cut with better quality at CHOP Shop for $15 My stylist was Nancy.
Had an iced latte and sea salt biscuit with butter and berry jelly!! Was super tasty, I love this place. I often see people I know from around town here hanging out great atmosphere and prices.

A friend and I went to Sabrina's for brunch on a late Sunday morning (3/14/21). Unfortunately there was 1.5 hour wait to dine in so we decided to place an order to go. We ordered stuffed French toast and Huevos Rancheros. The food was ready in about 25 minutes,  I had to ask the attendant at the door to look to see if my food was ready and it was sitting on the countertop for awhile. Needless to say the food wasn't hot so we had to warm it up when we got home. Overall the food was ok!

What a great event venue!  

This space is definitely one of Indy's hidden gems.  The students, faculty, and staff at the Ivy Tech Culinary and Conference Center really know their stuff.  The food was delightfully prepared, the facility was clean and well appointed, and the staff was friendly, knowledgeable, and helpful.  I really like the idea that much of the food is prepared by the students in the culinary program at Ivy Tech.

The space is very large and includes a good sized second-floor ballroom, along with smaller conference rooms which can be used for breakout sessions.  There is also a fairly large space on the first floor, which can be used as a ballroom, as well.  If you're looking for a space to host your next small to mid-size conference in Indy, definitely give this space a look!

This is by far one of my favorite stores. Add to that the fact that it's from my home town of Milwaukee. All of their spices are very fresh-- fresher than you can find anywhere else-- packaged in glass bottles (keeps them fresher, and is not toxic), and sold at prices comparable to what you'd find at a big box grocer (except for stuff like parsley, cilantro, garlic powder, black pepper balls, etc., which tend to run considerably higher). When you run out of a particular spice, you can buy it in a bulk package and just refill your jar. I've found that it's better to buy everything in the small jars (even though not as cost-effective at the outset) because, once you start shopping there and using their products, you really do become an addict. . . and will fast run out of space in your spice drawer/spice cabinet if you buy the large jars. They have every spice, herb, etc. imaginable, and they also have a ton of different mixes (for those who don't want to buy a bunch of different things and experiment on their own). Personally, I love using the "Sandwich Sprinkle" on tomatoes and salads (have yet to try it on a sandwich, since I don't make sandwiches at home), Arizona Dreaming in salsa and guacamole, Ruth Ann's Muskego Ave. Chicken and Fish Seasoning on tofu (though I'm sure it would also be fantastic on, well, chicken and fish), and the Mural of Flavor on pretty much everything. They also have a "33rd and Galena" spice that pays homage to their original location. They also sell dried lemon flakes, and orange flakes, which are great for people like me who don't keep fresh lemon or oranges around to grate, but need it for a recipe from time-to-time. They have more kinds of vanilla extract than you'd know what to do with, cake spice, anise, pumpkin spice, various kinds of cinnamon, nutmeg, etc. (they have a whole section devoted just to baking. . . and it's really cute!!!). You really can't go wrong stopping in here and browsing. Also, it helps that the employees are always really welcoming and really helpful (I suspect that many of them are more just working here to get out of the house and get some spending money than they are by necessity, so they're actually happy to be there)

23 dec 2018

update**

Three of us went, my wife had the corn and crab stuffed shrimp. Three small shrimp butterflied with a small amount of stuffing on top. They where not the sized shrimp one should use for stuffing. The large portion of mashed potatoes were under seasoned. The carrots and squash were good.

We had Lobster bisque which was good and presented well. We also had the artichoke dip which did not present well. but was tasty.

I had the ribs, which were tough as leather, I did not eat but one. I tasted the enormously over sized portion of mashed potatoes. They too were under seasoned and not eaten. The succotash was ok. 

The server and manager where both nice and took care of the issue properly, removing the uneaten plate of food and asking if I wanted a different meal, I did not.

The restaurant lights was to dark for my taste. I had to use the light of a phone to read the menu. We've been disappointed each of the last several times coming here.
Great customer service and fresh TASTY & DELICIOUS food!!! The burgers taste homemade and the wings were freshly fried and tossed beautifully in a mild sauce

My Peloton was delivered and set up quickly and professionally.  Both delivery guys were properly masked and socially distant.  They explained how to complete setup and made sure I had all the information I needed before they left.  Excellent job.
Delicious steamed dumplings! Shrimp lo mein and the egg rolls were tasty, all with fast delivery! I think the hot mustard packets could have been better...I like it super hot.

A beautiful property with stunning views of Tucson.  The outdoor areas have generous seating with fire seating placed with some distance for privacy.  The layout is a bit awkward.  A very small stairway to the second floor with the width of a fire escape.  The entry/valet area is undersized and cumbersome to use.  My room had a great patio, comfortable bed, and Olympic size bathtub.  A few ideas Loews should consider - lose some landscape in front add parking.  The access to hiking trails is wonderful.  Just a few short steps from the hotel are a bonus.  To be sure a nice place to stay, but not sure about the rep as a premium property.  I'll stay here again with AAA or similar discount.

This place is awesome! We went for lunch and had some mimosas as well as the crab cakes! Tremendous food! We wanted a little dessert so we order the French toast with blueberry compote that came with a side of bacon! What a treat! Service was great and the owner was very friendly!  This place is a must! We will be back for sure!
$8 for 5 pours, and a 10oz pour of your favorite, does it get any better?  Each beer we sampled was tasty.  It was hard to select my favorite.

Terrible mucho burrito location . Used to be a loyal mb fan . Driving from the west end to down town several days a week to eat mb . Unfortunately when some chains get big they also get stupid and arrogant . This location is a prime example of that . Staff refuse to serve items that are clearly on the menu .
Nice little quaint place to grab some glasses of wine. While there we tried the apple fritter, which was great. Nothing like some diced caramelized apples, pastry dough, powdered sugar...

I ordered a medium thin crust pizza, boneless buffalo wings and a 2L of Coke. It took almost an hour but the driver did call to say there was a mix up at the store and that she was on the way. When I got my order the pizza was cold and cut into squares. When I called they told me that's how the thin crust comes (even though there is nothing that states that on their website!!). The rest of the order was just fine.  The person I talked to asked the manager and they sent out another pizza with a regular cut. When the 2nd pizza came it was cut correctly and HOT! They did a great job making up for their mistake!

Booked this before our trip and got to the dock about 9:30. Boarding process was pretty easy. Tables are first come first served so don't try to save seats- there were some folks doing this and they got corrected quickly.  The boat goes about an hour upriver to the battlefield of the war of 1812 with Charles giving much history on the way. We docked and were able to go looking around the site and the tiny museum plus the large monument dedicated to the site. You can listen to a ranger explain things but we could t hear him well so struck out on our own. It was fascinating history but I don't think I would take his trip a second time. On the way back downriver food was served buffet style and I have to admit it truly exceeded my expectations. There was red beans and rice which was smoky and flavorful, a gumbo with a deep rich roux, jumbalaya that was more tomatoey than I was used to, and a DELICIOUS seafood pasta with a rich cream sauce. Excellent. They also had salad and cornbread muffins which I didn't try. The bread pudding with a white chocolate rum sauce was excellent. 
   The ride back was a great history of the Katrina disaster from someone who lived it. Charles pointed out many examples of FEMA's shame. All in all a good tour, though you would have to be way more invested in history to get a lot out of the battlefield. A good family trip and the drinks from he bar are good and strong.

Frank repaired my 20+ year old builtin SubZero frig by replacing the ice maker. He called to keep me up to date on parts arrival and installed the new ice maker on time. After 1 day, I had a drawer full of ice with cubes that did not stick together!
He also cleaned the heat exchanger/fan for a reasonable $85 every 2 years.
Great service, good communication, quality work!

Tony

We found this place on yelp and only live a few minutes away so we're excited to try it. We had a little trouble finding a spot to park but walked in at 1:20 and it was still bustling. We were greeted right away and everyone seemed happy to be there. My husband got the Reuben and I got the Grown up grilled cheese. They were both incredible. My husband polished off his sandwich, the house made chips and his coleslaw and he normally won't touch his sides. My grilled cheese was perfectly toasted and had gooey cheese that went on forever. My fries were so hot and amazing that it was hard to stop eating them and focus on the grilled cheese. We were so glad that we found this place and definitely will be back again soon!

It was salad.  Nothing much more to say about it... except that it was a bit overpriced for what you get.

The Chopped Water is ridiculously overpriced at $1.50 -- make sure you get the coupon by texting the number on their signs if you want to try it.

I had to stop in the middle of eating to write this review and I never write reviews. The Belgium waffle and bacon here is the best breakfast I've ever had and the bartenders are really pretty! Enjoy!

I utilized this hotel for a business event - we booked meeting space, catering of breakfast, 2 lunches, and a cocktail hour - plus multiple refreshment breaks. Despite the weather being iffy, the event was amazing. Onur and Tom were fabulous . . . always thinking on their feet as we needed to adjust due to rain and a tornado watch. Both lunches  were supposed to be held outside, but they adjusted quickly and moved us into the restaurant with a view. The bell hops and front desk personnel were great as well, as they unloaded tons of event materials and gave out gift baskets for our attendees as they checked in. The gal who served at our cocktail hour was wonderful too - I wish I remembered her name so I could send kudos to her manager. By the way - the food was great - we fed 35 people over the course of 2 days and had nothing but positive feedback. We had great service all around!

As for the rooms, the bad one or two bad reviews I read was not at all what ANY of us experienced - and we had 22 rooms with ZERO complaints. All rooms have an ocean view, and there is a shuttle that will drive you across to the beach if you need sand. The rooms smelled nice and there was no mold anywhere. As far as smoking goes, none of my neighbors must have smoked. Almost all of us slept with our porch doors open the entire night because the breeze and the ocean atmosphere was fabulous. I never smelled smoke once. 

All in all, a great experience, lovely rooms and staff, and a perfect place for a destination event. Thanks to all who helped out!

Sandwiches were fast and spot on. Restaurant and restrooms were clean. Employees were friendly. There was a young African American man working this afternoon (1pm on 11/27), I didn't catch his name but he was doing a great job keeping the machines clean, greeting the customers, checking to make sure our food was good. We even put on gloves and cleaned up the parking lot. Seemed like a very hard worker and deserved the thumbs up

Awesome! I was visiting from San Diego and did not expect to find this quality of raw vegan in St. Pete Beach. Tacos were yummy as was sushi. I had never seen vegan raw pad Thai before and thus had to try it. You guessed it - delicious! It's also worth adding that the owner remained open an hour after normal closing time just for the two of us. We were so impressed by the Caesar dressing we ordered salads to go (with dressing on the side) for lunch the next day. A++++

Moved to the area recently, and it's so hard to find honest  and won't make you pay for things that aren't needed (especially as a female).  There were a few things that needed done, but the big things like the tires I thought I needed, weren't necessary. I appreciate the honesty and I will come back again!

What amazes me is the way the Plainfield Hotbox rates compared to the Avon location. The Avon store gets a perfect for service, quality and the professionalism the youth display running this store.The Plainfield location was severely lacking in many areas.
If you are going to order - you are better off using the Avon location!

These folks are fantastic. Their office was clean and bright. They were as quick as can be with the full set of x-rays and cleaning. Very friendly and gentle. I loved the use of the little camera - made things so much easier to understand and see!

Love them - will go here for all my dental work. Thank you!

If you offered 10 stars I would give them to the Fairy Godmother of petsitting!  I have a challenge for a dog sitter....6 dogs, pekes and pugs with 5 of them under the age of 5.  Totally untrained and CRAZY!  Barb is so good with them.  We always go over everything before I go away to what their favorite treat of the month is to where each food bowl needs to go.  She always writes a complete report on all the fun they had while I was gone too.  I have her come two times a day because I am a nervous mama.  The house looks great when I come back with the mail inside.  Barb has helped me for over two years and I wouldn't use anyone else.  We love you Fairy Godmother!

In from the west coast, looking for something different. Home run here! Attention by the wait staff is warming, real and refreshing!! Make sure to consider a small place like this is focused on quality in meal preparation and your experience with minimal (but super friendly) staff supporting the effort so it takes a while. Think Caribbean grab a Red Stripe lager and chill, don't worry, be happy....The food is worth the wait!!
Love their macarons, yum and their drinks are delicious definitely recommend their passion fruit juices with the lychee jellies.

I wish my work wasn't so close to Madewell, merely because I find myself speed trying on clothing during too many lunch breaks. My trips to Madewell are always rushed, as such, but I still manage to receive excellent service every time. 

The store has such beautiful items for viewing, but I typically stick to the sale room. Their sale has a lot of 30% off days, so I recommend waiting until that rolls around. (They will still put sale on sale even when online does not). Madewell is a dream in ordering online from the store, everything always goes seamlessly. 

My only complaint with this particular store is their sale isn't always accurate. Many times I have found items marked up in store higher than online (sale items only). The sales ladies are happy to make the adjustment, I just find it odd that they don't have accurate pricing. 

Deals: 
-15% off with a student I.D. 
-Currently running a promotion for $20 off new pair of jeans when you bring in an old pair (any brand- bejeweled booty included) as they are using denim for insulation of homes for unfortunate families, nice idea!

Mediocre service, mediocre steak or "Onglet à l'échalote." My husband's chicken dish was good. The beer menu earned the second star.  I've had a much better steak and sides (veggies, not crap french fries) at Longhorn's.
The most awesome meal I've had in Midtown ever. Service was outstanding. Dinner was a cornucopia of flavors.

I absolutely loved how simple and straight forward their menu options are; nothing fancy nor complicated. Also, I've never had a baked potato with a burger and it was actually a great mix! Probably my only recommendations to the restaurant are that the cheese would've been nicer melted and the bacon bits aren't that good. But other than that, the food was very tasty and yummy!

Great BBQ, the meat is all dry-rubbed and you pick whichever sauce you like. The staff is very friendly. 

My only gripe is the limited beer selection. Blue Moon was the only non-AB beer they sold unfortunately. I could have used a Shiner to wash down their BBQ meat products...

This place is always packed. Staff are attentive and nice. Usually I get seated near the windows and stare at the abandon bowling alley lol I'm fine with the view, it makes me really wonder what have ever happened to it. Pho is always good here like the way it's suppose to be. This place will not disappoint!

Location is great. Drinks are good. Service is pretty good. Food is way overpriced and mediocre but that is to be expected when you're on the water. Atmosphere is like you're not in St Pete but on an island somewhere. You're paying for the location.

Went for dinner tonight!  Sit outside on patio.  Table cleaned off-no silverware.  Received drinks still no silverware or napkins.  Ordered appetizer-still no silverware or napkins.  Finally had to ask for them.  Then meals came out before salads.  Really...Don't think I will be going back here!!!

Last week I took Rt 7 and Rt 19 buses to get to the airport.  Arrived back today, and reversed the trip.  I had the stops written down in my cell phone.  I listened carefully for the stops to be announced. Had no problem until the last leg of the trip on the Rt 7 bus.  My stop was announced, I immediately dinged the call bell.  The driver continued on past my stop.  I called to her that she had missed my stop.  She told me I hadn't rung.  I reiterated that I HAD.  She told me I should have paid attention, WHICH I HAD BEEN, VERY CAREFULLY, since it was full dark outside and I couldn't see a thing and don't live on that street anyway so wouldn't know any landmarks.  I was VERY careful to listen for my stop.  

Finally after arguing with me back and forth, she stopped and let me out. I had no idea how many stops she had skipped.  I asked how far back the stop I wanted (Echo @ Mt. Babcock) was and she told me she didn't know.  I am disabled, I walk very poorly with a cane, the EXPECTED walk back would have been bad enough, but she dumped me somewhere I did not know where in the dark and freezing windy cold.  I had to call my son to find out how far I had to walk back.  My cell phone often does not work, thank god it worked this time.  She kept telling me it was my fault for not paying attention, only I HAD been paying attention and I dinged the dinger as soon as my stop was announced.

SHE wasn't paying attention and then she was mean about it and dismissive and wouldn't even tell me how far I needed to walk back to get to where I was SUPPOSED to have been let off.  I would like to add she was also rude to an older man for just closing his eyes for a minute, something I had done SEVERAL times during the trip myself, and she rudely told him her "rule" was that there was no sleeping on the bus.  He wasn't sleeping and she didn't even address him, she kept yelling at some other guy who wasn't even sitting near him to "wake his friend up".  None of us on the bus at that point knew who or what she was talking about, and in point of fact I had been glancing back that way and had seen the guy close his eyes for just a few seconds before she started yelling at people in general apparently.  Finally the guy she was mad about having closed his eyes realized HE was the topic of conversation and popped his eyes open in surprise and said "I'm not even asleep!"  

It was right after this that she blew right past my stop.  I don't know what her problem is but maybe she shouldn't be taking her personal problems out on us old folks.  I guess I am lucky I was sitting sideways so she couldn't see me close my eyes or she would have admonished me for daring to close my eyes for a few seconds too.  I had no complaint about any other driver.  I do not normally ride the bus at all.  I used to have a disabled person card but I let it lapse because I was told I had to buy tickets 10 at a time and as I rarely go out that was not terribly useful to me.  This is the first time I was going to see my grandson in another state and had to get to the airport. A cab ride is $55 so I thought to ride the bus to the airport and back and did so successfully until this woman ignored my stop request and then blamed me for her mistake.  It wouldn't have made me so angry had she just said something like "I'm sorry, I didn't hear the bell", and then told me how far I would have to walk back instead of telling me she doesn't know where the stops are on her own route. There is no excuse for the way she treated me or the older man she so rudely chastised for daring to close his eyes.  And btw, are HER rules different from RTC rules?  Do her "rules" supersede the norms of polite society as well as RTC rules?  It took me 22 minutes to make that walk, which google thinks is a 7 minute walk - that would be because I am disabled. I was prepared to walk from the Mt. Babcock and Echo stop but not the Bismark and Echo stop.  I didn't even know where the stop where she finally let me out actually was, no idea how many stops she had passed after blowing past mine. I'm just lucky my phone worked this time so I could get hold of my son in another state to tell me where I was and how far I had to walk back to get to where I should have been to start with.

There are a BUNCH of complaints already here about treatment of the elderly and disabled. Clearly RTC doesn't give a crap, they just want to take in the grant money for supposedly providing support services to elderly/disabled without actually PROVIDING said services. I guess the fact that I am elderly AND disabled gave this woman free rein to treat me like something nasty stuck to the bottom of her shoe. RTC clearly agrees with her. You know, because someone for whom walking an extra block (or more since she wouldn't tell me) in the dark freezing windy cold on an unfamiliar street is a real problem, must be a subhuman who doesn't deserve air to breathe, let alone the use of her precious bus or any respect whatsoever.

This is a decent place for chinese take out. I enjoy their crab Rangoon and chicken with garlic sauce. I've never dined in here so I can't speak for that. The lady on the phone is a bit rude at times. If u can ignore that aspect, the portion size is pretty decent for the price.

This review is based on my first visit to this new liquor store that recently opened in an old Liquor Depot location. 

Wow! This place is awesome and will be my new go to place for all of my liquor needs. It is huge and has such a wide variety of stock. A growler and tasting bar is at the very back. I can't wait to come back and try that out. There is a massive line of beer coolers and you can get beers from all over. There is a gluten free beer section as well. They also have some singles so you can try out something new.   Wine and spirits take over a large chunk of the store. Great selections. Lots of alcohol related gifts and gadgets too. 

Staff were plentiful and friendly. Lots of shared parking with the mall. 

I'm so glad this one is close to home too! If you live around the Southgate Mall area you have to check this out. You will not be disappointed!

Went in tonight with 3 items. 4 people talking at the customer service counter and the light was on for express checkout. Why i come back here is beyond me. I guess its the only game in town. The amount of expired items ive bought here is crazy. You need to look at the dates. On a good note the employees at the seafood and meat counter are great.

I went to Metro carwash and paid for a detail it isn't cheap. I had to point out to them they didn't wash around Wheel wells and they didn't wash out the bed of the truck . I guess I will go somewhere else.
Bbq shrimp ! Visited last November and I'm still dreaming of this shrimp in a peppery butter sauce. Go for lunch and 1.25$ martinis. Classic NOLA restaurant.
We had barbecue from 317 and it was excellent. Moist and the seasoning on the pork was perfect. I would recommend this to anyone

This is the best restaurant my family and I have ever stumbled upon. Our dinner was so good we went the next day for lunch. The staff was fast and friendly. The prices are great and the servings are greater than what you pay for. It's family friendly and cafe style. 

After trying three different entrees, two appetizers, a kids menu item and having a couple different drinks, I can't criticize a thing. 

Try the spring roll bowl if you are very hungry and any of the fried cauliflower options are great appetizers. 

I wish there were one if these in Chicago.
When we're craving wings, Ale is our go to place!  The service, food, and drinks are always great here!

A word of warning, this is deer tick city in the summer. So if you happen to be there in the July heat stay out of the grass. Aside from that this is a pleasant little park, with updated bathroom facilities and a well maintained walking path. I should also note they upkeep it quite well in the winter too, and with it being so close to my house, I often go there for a refreshing walk. Though I should mention it's really only good for walking or taking kids to the playground; there's no picnic facilities or gaming areas.

The price was a little higher than what I would pay at a smaller shop but I was in a crunch and they got the job done. My prints turned out great and were ready within a few minutes. Only 3 stars because the prints were much more costly than I was quoted and because the service was a 3 stars.

Dr. Williams is an excellent optometrist and I have gone to her for over 3 years. She is knowledgeable,patient, and just has a very kind, nice way about her. I would highly recommend her.
On the other hand, I would definitely not recommend getting your eyeglasses at Lenscrafters. I have bought glasses there for the past three years and have noticed the prices have increased along with the amount of problems I have experienced. I think you will find that once the price of all the add on options which you are told is so necessary you could go to an independent eye glass store and get better service, better eyeglasses, and people highly skilled in making glasses without the possibility that trainees will make your eyeglasses without double-checking the product before the customers gets it. It happened to me once and I was fortunate that an employee there - after i complained i could not see right- checked to find out that they were made by trainees that very busy day and were not double- checked before they given to customers that day.. I appreciate the employee's honesty but I would not be comfortable buying glasses there again knowing how loosely they run things.

Beautiful and serene place to relax and enjoy a cocktail. I had the Kentucky Peach which was delicious.  The bourbon paired with a dash of the bourbon barrel aged maple syrup is a fantastic combination.
Great for lunch buffet. Spicier than most which is great and staff is very attentive. Great chutney.

I love ice cream and for me, this was just okay.  The ice cream was good, the service was okay, the price was a bit high, and it was not too dirty.  One complaint was they were out of a lot of flavors and they do not have soft serve.  

The location is cool as you can walk down to the river and watch the ships go by.  

If you want decent ice cream and are in the area, this place will fit your needs without many complaints.

All the food was fresh and healthy. We got a quinoa bowl, gyro, and hummus appetizer. They were good portion sized foods and everything was sooo yummy!! Staff was also very friendly and accommodating.

Great place, awesome unpretentious vibe, the girl that poured our wine was super knowledgeable, attentive, and even gave us a few tips on where to hang out and eat in SB.  They ran out of the wines on the tasting menu but they ended up just giving us an extra pour of whatever we wanted.  Wines were so so, or else I probably would have given this place 5 stars.  The cab-syrah blend was my fave.

*Shrimp and grits*
*waffle and chicken with a side of bacon* (not pictured home fries, Cuban bread with butter) because we are a tad greedy. I was extremely excited to come and eat at this place. Nice Cute and welcoming spot with friendly and attentive staff.  Chicken and waffles by far my favorite.
Richard went out of his way to help me with a registration + renewal as I am new to the area. He was generous with his time and was very helpful with information. Looking forward to returning!

Maybe I am getting old, but I am over the Bourbon Street/Canal Street/French Quarter scene. I enjoy the taste of certain drinks, I'm not in it to throw up and forget the evening, and I'd rather have a nice dinner than an all day bender, so staying in the Garden District just makes sense.

Great hotel -- Hampton Inns have the best beds around -- in a great neighborhood with easy access via trolley to whatever you want to do downtown. Of all the Hilton properties in the area, this is your best value with the best location.

I don't hang around South Street very often, but when I do, you will usually find me at Mako's. I'm sitting in front of a video-crack machine with a can of PBR in hand, like a classy lady that I am.

Mako's offers the Philly special for $5: PBR or High Life accompanied by a shot of choice - Jager, Cuervo, Jim, Jack, or Stoli. I'm a tequila girl. I chase it with a shot of their bloody mary mix. Again, class to the max.

The bar looks run-down, bathrooms are a bit scary, and clientele is a bit rough around the edges. However, if you're looking for a place to let it all hang out and enjoy the city's cheapiest drinks, look no further than this little dive.
Great food and atmosphere. Perfect huge corner booths for large families, that made dining more comfortable. Service was quick and attentive. Definitely one of the best restaurants in Reno!
