I've been a customer of this location for close to 13 years. From the time they opened. Today we ordered $60 worth of food through Uber. It was to be delivered less than 5 minutes from the location. It took over an hour. That's not the issue. The food had a nasty smell to it like rotten vegetables. It was inedible. Not going to be back, can't stomach it after the smell of rotten food.

So what incites a just North of Kennedy Lass to make the trek to Tarpon Springs? (Well yes, Gyros, but that's another Yelp altogether.)  The answer would be an empty wine fridge, a few weeks living bottle-to-bottle and a few too many Total Wine trips featuring big-name, boring, $15 everyday bottles. I may be confined to my libation budget but always dream the decantable bottle dream (perhaps, on someone else's AMEX, any givers?). This place has many labels that are "highly rated" as well as some undercover future favorites.  B-21 also maintains a noteworthy selection of Spirits and varied tastings throughout the year. 
(Tip-worthy:  B-21 offers free delivery for cases of 12 on the 21st of every month if you are not a Wine-Trekkie such as myself.)

All the ladies are amazing! They always do an amazing job.  I went to them for pellets when other places said I just had to deal with menopause. Apparently, I had a .2 testosterone count and definitely needed to be treated. Thanks ladies!

The wait might be long (take a newspaper or the latest gossip magazine), but it's worth it. The most authentic Mexican Food I've ever tasted, comparable to a lot of the food we've enjoyed in Mexico. Also a fun place to take friends who've never had a true Santa Barbara experience. Friends always ask me which dish I most recommend, and that is difficult since everything we've tried is delicious.

MA

The movers did an excellent job! They were fast, friendly, and careful with our things. They were a little bit late on arrival, but called us in advance to let us know exactly how late they would be (which was only about a half hour late). There was also some confusion and miscommunication with the office at first, but we worked it out and Kayla  (the office girl) was very helpful and fast with her responses. I would definitely recommend "All In A Box Movers"  if you want good quality, friendly and fast movers, and a great price!

I came here last year for dinner with a friend who has special dietary concerns and can be somewhat difficult when he doesn't get exactly what he wants exactly when he wants it. The staff here was incredibly courteous and compliant to his demands despite some outright rude comments on his part. As far as the food goes, it is very good and would normally be a four star rating, but the wait staff did everything they could to earn this rating and succeeded.

I ate here several times during a conference and really enjoyed the food. I had the scallops, grilled asparagus, the pumpkins raviolis, and grilled artichoke - all very good. I ate at both the bar and the restaurant. The restaurant is lovely, service good, relatively quiet, and comfortable. The bar is lively and very busy at happy hour

Two needs improvement. The first is the pricing on the wine list. The mark up is egregious. I don't mind paying a mark up as businesses have to make money however this was ridiculous. 

The second needs improvement is on bar service. They are totally understaffed and have a bad attitude, possibly from understaffing as they were hustling really hard during happy hour. This shows up by them not making eye contact with you and literally having to almost physically grab them to get a drink. 

I ordered a gin and tonic which tasted awful, bad tonic water that tasted like chlorine and no quinine, I had a really hard time getting their attention and my colleague was ready for his second drink before we were able to finally flag them over. The bartender then was a little put out that I didn't want the drink and still left it on the tab. They took it off after implying that I drank it, really? 

Not sure if management is trying to cut costs by inadequate staffing but I can tell you that you are losing money on sales because you can't give adequate service at the bar. I would also talk with your bartenders about customer service culture

I was very impressed with the service provided by The Greenwood location. I was having trouble deciding where to get my windows tinted and what to have done. The person working the desk and taking calls was very helpful and answered all questions. She was very friendly and seemed genuinely interested in helping. Everything was thoroughly explained from making an appointment, down payment, pricing, tint differences, to cancellation policy.

I took my car in one morning and dropped it off. I had standard tint applied to all side windows and back window of a 4 door car. I also had a brow put on the windshield. The work was done in a couple hours (pretty quick IMO). The quality is fantastic. I have noticed no issues since the tint was applied. I have been very pleased with the work and would choose Tint King for future vehicles!
Great dinner spot.  Excellent service. My parents came to visit for the weekend from about 6 hours away and we chose this spot for their first night in town.  I was very impressed. Will be back!

The colourful exterior drew me in to this unique antique shop. It is a converted house with the garage also used as a retail area. Sometimes it feels like going through a maze to get around and see everything on display, but it is worth it. Most of the items are from country life, but also include clothing, games, and toys. Prices vary and the owner is absolutely wonderful. Worth checking out if you are in the Highlands area.

Great selection of healthy options with fresh, seasonal ingredients. For all my gluten-free friends they have a small but tasty GF selection. I enjoyed the great service. I was there on a Friday lunch so tables were a 30 minute wait so we sat at the bar. The bar staff were fun, attentive and friendly. A great spot - I highly recommend especially if you are a shoe shopping, GF lover like me! (oh the shoe shopping is just because I was at Nordstroms!)

TWO New Orleans locals told me that one of best fried chicken they've had was at....Popeye's. This Popeye's. So of course, we had to see if this was indeed true. 

There was No Difference from any other Popeye's. 

Not that it was bad. It just wasn't special, especially when compared the best fried chicken we did have, which was was Coop's Place. Also, the ordering and getting your food process is rather convoluted.
Worst overhead music in town. If you like annoying music, very loud while you're gaming, this is the place for you.

The food is really good.
It reminds me of the flavor of home.
price is ok and very clean

Good food nice and fresh... The side salad is pretty big and has potato salad and fresh vegetables. I had a decent side order that was ready in 20 minutes to take out. Plenty of food...had dinner then lunch The next day

Dr. Cohn and her team at Fishtown Animal Hospital are the best in the business! I have been to numerous other vets with my pets throughout the years and no one comes close to Fishtown Animal Hospital. From the moment you walk in the door and until you walk out you feel like you are a part of the family. Dr. Cohn is knowledgable and treats you and your pet with the utmost respect and care. We are beyond happy with Fishtown Animal Hospital and love each visit. Thanks for taking great care of Lenny, he loves you guys!

Love, love, love this place. Super nice staff and cleanliness throughout. Their gym section is huge and no waits for treadmills or bikes. The basketball courts can be really packed at peak hours and weekends. Lockers are nice and tidy, and the showers have actual HOT water(women's locker room). The warm pool area is "cleaned" for debris once an hour and takes about 3 minutes or so, (basically everyone has to get out of the pools until they're done). There's also a jacuzzi, sauna, and 6(?) lap lanes (max 2 people per lane).

When you're a regular and you go at the same time and do your routine, you often also find others that do the same and bump into them every time. Nice way for small talk while you're working out or even getting to know some people around the area.
Great place for an all American breakfast at a great value. Good food, good people, and a friendly atmosphere. Comfort food at its best. I would recommend this Biscuits to everyone.

My partner and I visited the restaurant for half priced margaritas.. We were at the restaurant approximately 43 minutes.. was not to impressed with the food however given our meals were $5 & $6 each, I let it go.. when receiving our ticket i noticed we were charged full price on the margarita pitcher. I asked the waiter (assuming he forgot to mark it half price or system error) why we were being charged full price for our drinks..  he gave me a very big grin and said he'd have to talk to his manager the deal runs from 3pm to close. Typically I'd bite it, our mistake for not reading the fine print.. I looked back over the ticket to notice the ticket had been opened at 2:39.. really? NOW with this being said rules are rules but the waiter couldn't of thought to mention waiting a couple of minutes? Assuming the smile he gave and how quickly he jumped to speaking with the manager he knew that he that was wrong.. he returned to the table and told us his manager could not fix the issue. I had to pull out the "I need to speak to your manager card" which is honestly a card I have only ever pulled out twice in my lifetime.. the manager arrives at our table and explains to me we missed the deal by a few minutes, agrees that our ticket price "sucks" yet also REFUSES to make it right because he would get in trouble with his boss?  I do not appreciate an up charge and i do not appreciate someone refusing make a situation right especially after agreeing with the fact that it was a bit of a slick move. Noticing they both had the same smile on their faces left our server with no tip & no returning customers. I suggest to whomever the owner is, if your manager can agree to something being wrong yet cannot take the proper steps to correct it because they fear getting in trouble - you need to re-evaluate how you run a business and a staff.

This was our second time at Pine State Biscuits and once again it did not disappoint! We got the Reggie, Reggie deluxe and coffee. We ordered our sandwiches "hot" which means they douse the fried chicken in hot sauce. It was delicious and I highly recommend if you like an added kick! Last time we were there we got the fried green tomatoes and they were incredible. We didn't get them this time because the sandwiches are so huge that you don't really need anything else. The line the get in is long on the weekends and it takes a bit to get through but by the time you do there is usually a seat readily available and you get served within 5-10 minutes of sitting down.

They did a wonderful job repaying our driveway. Everyone who worked at our house was professional and went above and beyond my expectations. They came when they said they would, and completed the job in the timeframe specified. My property looks great and wouldn't hesitate to use Orlando and his crew again! I highly recommend HD paving!!

Most horrifying experience EVER!  Been there before,  they are always out of stuff on their menu,  but wanted two give them a chance. ...went in to eat,  had to use the bathroom to wash my hands,  it looked like someone had just washed the floor. ..I grabbed the faucet to turn on the water and the handle had throw-up (puck) all over it! !! Now all over my hand!  Also all over the trash can!!!  I Freaked Out!  UNBELIEVABLE!  Nice cleaning job ! I threw a fit in front of everyone! !! How can something like that happen???   HORRIBLE DIRTY PLACE. !  : (

I've tried some gyros before and have always been a fan of Greek food (mostly gyros) but haven't really encountered the wow factor until I came to this place.  It's a small place and you'd probably miss it unless you're really looking for it but trust me, you'd want to look for it!  I had the lunch special and the gyro turned out really delicious, the meat was not chewy which I've had before from other places and the sauce was really good.  The meat was literally melt-in-your-mouth goodness and is so much more flavorful than any other Greek places I've tried.  After eating about half of my gyro, I wish I wasn't full already because it was so sad to not be able to eat the rest.  I definitely want to come back and try their other menu items.  While waiting for my food, I could smell all the different blends of aroma from the kitchen and they just smelled so delicious!

The place is nice and well-kept and like several people mentioned before, it's family-ran and they all seem so nice.  I went during lunchtime and it was busy; some people had to wait to place their orders but great food is always worth the wait and what's another 10 minutes for something delicious and reasonably priced?  I did notice that their menu items are very reasonably-priced.  It's definitely a place to try if you like Greek food.

We met a few friends who were staying at the hotel at the outside pool bar. Such a great experience all around.  Initial impression was  quaint and lit up front porch that just oozed with romantic style.The interior decor, style, and vibe in the common areas is one of eclectic comfort and beauty! The pool area was absolutely stunning and one that could hold a candle to some a luxury resort property. The bathroom area was impeccably clean and beautifully designed. We had such amazing service from Michael the bartender. He was the only one covering the bar and surrounding tables and his attention was perfect. Never did we have to wait or ask for anything. When people were looking for drink suggestions and some ideas, he asked questions of what we liked, and then offered numerous suggestions. When frozen drinks were asked for, we giggled and said "are you going to kill us" and he said absolutely not I'm here to take care of you. He gave last call due to the the quiet hours around the pool, but extended upon request with manager's approval. It was such an accommodating place with true customer service. Such a breath of fresh air to be treated so well. We had a friend with us that had an ankle surgery and even though she wasn't staying at the hotel, they kindly drove her in their free shuttle.

Nice little shop in a quaint shopping area. Has a cute ATM cupcake machine right up front. Cupcakes are nice and moist. I got the coconut which was tasty. The frosting is very sweet (a little too sweet for me). Nice selection with a variety of flavors. Definitely not cheap. Half a dozen is about $22.

Really awesome breakfast place! I had the Baja Omelette, which was absolutely delicious (I love how it has avocados in it!) and came with a great sauce on top. The cut fruit in the fruit cup had a slightly weird taste--must have been the preservative coating--but nothing so strong that it stopped me from eating it. I was a little disappointed that when I ordered mango juice it wasn't house-made but Naked juice (which isn't bad, still). The service was great too, and a guy that works there--or owns the place?--was very friendly and talkative. It was also a little pricey for breakfast fare, but all in all a good experience, I'd recommend, and I'd go back!

I recently had lunch at the Glasshouse Bistro at the Enjoy Centre in St Albert. 
I really enjoy coming here for brunch/lunch since they use all local and organic ingredients. 

I had the soba noodle and roasted beets salad for $14 with an Earl Grey tea. 
This was one of the best salads I've had in a restaurant in a long time! So good! Roasted walnuts, white beans were also in this salad. It was such an interesting mix! 

One thing is since this restaurant is in a greenhouse, I find the temperature can go up or down. It was quite warm the day I went with the sun beaming in. Great atmosphere though!
Excellent service. Good food!  Server was super friendly and helpful. Nice casual atmosphere with good food. Alligator sausage was excellent.

Worst experience ever. I understand that it's  after new years but that no reason to show a terrible attitude to paying customer. Seamless told me the meal was accepted and in the process of being made. Never made it to my door. This place leave you irritated and even hungrier. Deserves to be shutdown
Amazing gluten free options, love the atmosphere here, and looks like a great drink selection. Wish they had gluten free beer options though!

Kim is the best! I tried her out with a Groupon, which was such a great deal.  I loved our conversations and her genuine personality really hooked me.  The other thing that sticks out to me about her is her love for nails. It's so refreshing to be around someone that puts great effort into something they care about.  She is super professional, clean, on time, and has a MILLION colors! (Always new colors that she adds too). 

She offers refreshments, and even got me a little gift at Christmas. Oh and nails are always fab, they still look pretty damn good after three weeks.

100% Recommend

We took our family to this restaurant and had a great experience. As someone with limited exposure to German food, I asked a lot of questions. Our server was knowledgeable and very patient with me. 

They had a gluten-free menu for me, which was great. I had the Eggplant Schnitzel (GF) and enjoyed it. Our family enjoyed a wide variety of foods from the dumplings to the quail and the macaroni and cheese (kids menu). It is definitely a unique experience. The decor and atmosphere were inviting in this hidden gem. If you like German food and are looking for an adventure, you've gotta go!

I've been going to DK Auto Repair for a couple of years now. A good friend of mine recommended Dave and he's never disappointed. DK Auto now works on all of our family cars and he's always done an outstanding job. He's professional, reliable and most importantly honest. One of my car's brakes were squeaking while I backed up. I dropped it off expecting a call to aurhorize major brake work. Imagine my surprise when he told me there was absolutely nothing wrong with them. It's a great feeling to drop off your car with absolute confidence that it's in good hands and that you'll be treated with exceptional fairness. I highly recommend that you give DK Auto Repair a chance to earn your business and trust.

First auto shop I've been at where everyone is busy working, running around, and have the nicest attitude when you walk in. Very friendly, got my car in right away, and beat Franklin Discount Tire pricing by $100.

My family and I are regulars at O'Charley's in Franklin,TN. If it wasn't for GERARD C. My family and I would probably stop visiting the restaurant. Gerard is our definition of GREAT customer service and Dedication to his work. He goes out of his way to make sure my family has everything we need and making our visits the best.  I gave O'Charley's 3 stars!!!!Gerard gets 5!!! Which brings me to my point. The majority of the other employees ( young kids) show no work ethic or care. One girl I saw walked out of the kitchen digging in her teeth. A young lady up front hosting throwing crumbled up paper at another employee. 2 employees chasing each other. Then there is a gentlemen that works upfront hosting with short black hair sort of tall. He is rude,has no manners, and no people skills. Every single time we are in the restaurant and he is working. It's the same experience with him...

It's a place with an amazing collection of stuff, located in the heart of the Bywater. All kinds of inventory here, ranging from antique furniture, costumes, knick knacks and general curiosities. A terrific place to waste some time looking at stuff you can't live without. Recently however, the prices have gone up, you see prices that mention the "rental" price for a lot of the really weird stuff. I am sure the movie prop people have made they way here and the increased in Hollywood money has jacked up some of the prices.

Our family visited Rasa Indian Cuisine for dinner last evening - our first trip together to an Indian restaurant and it was fabulous!  First the restaurant is beautiful with a peaceful calm decor. We were quickly seated in a very comfortable booth and served water. The menu includes a broad selection of vegetarian and non-vegetarian appetizers and entrees, and several vegan selections as well. We ordered 2 apps - mango shrimp and spicy fried cauliflower and 3 entrees - tandoori salmon, tandoori chicken and aloo gobi for the four of us and it was plenty of food. Food was hot, fresh and delicious!  Plenty of naan also.  Service was excellent.  It's also BYOB!!
I would definitely recommend!
There was also a children's menu and a large party room if that's of interest to you.

I have been eating here while on work trips! I sit in the bar and the bartender, Jama?, is great! I love going to places that make you feel welcome and treat you like a friend! My food was always good, hot, and to order! I will return!

This is one of our go to spots after class for good food and wine. Their prices are reasonable and the food is great. The Nachos are amazing and I tried their Cobb Salad last night for the first time and was very impressed with how fresh it was. 
The one negative is that the service can be a bit slow, so just be aware before you go :)
Okay but not great.  Burgers were undersized and okay. Fun experience but not a food hotspot.

Was at a Bowling Tournament in Reno at the Grand Sierra Resort. They have a Johnny Rockets there. We phone ordered what we wanted for in between Doubles and Team games.
All was good with the exception that they don't have a complete menu. But only one of us was impacted. No Black Bean Burger.

Food was ready and still hot when I got there to pick up. Burgers was tasty.

Must try!
Flavors are delicious...and the employees behind the counter are very informative. Didn't know what to order. Told the person what flavors I liked, he made some suggestions, and he found two complimentary flavors that I could eat together. I  am from California...if ever in Arizona again, I will definitely, come back!!

My friends' bands play here often so I've been here somewhat frequently.  The food is good and so is the coffee but I need to complain about the service behind the bar (at night).  I'm hoping they see this and make some changes.  

They are RUDE.  Every time I've been there, I've had a hard time with a bartender.  When I asked for a coffee downstairs, the barista/bartender actually GROANED because he didn't feel like making it.  All they do is grab a can of beer and serve it to you, so I understand it takes more time to actually make a coffee than grab a can of beer and open it for me, but you do serve coffee.  When I gave him a tip of $2.50 on a $3 coffee (for his trouble), he didn't thank me.  Other times, they've given me a hard time for ordering water (god forbid I want to hydrate) nor do they ask if you want bottled or tap.  And they're just in general, RUDE RUDE RUDE every time.  I'm going to stop being nice and tipping well for their trouble of opening a can of beer for me because I'm so sick of their attitude.  

Secondly, I think they charge way too much for canned beers.  

I hope management improves this.

I cannot seem to get off the James Bond girl drinks page of the menu when I go to Goosed.  I love trying all the fun drinks.  Pussy Galore is my  favorite.  They also have the Almond Joy martini, yum.  Anything with whip cream on the rim.. I'm on it.  We did NYE at  Goosed for 5 dollar martinis.  It was cheap, fun and the sexy blonde bartender was mesmerizing.  I have never had bad service at Goosed.  A++

I recently switched my oldest here along with my newest addition. They have two very convenient locations, one Uptown and in Metairie. All of the doctors are friendly. Staff is also very helpful. Both my kids sees Dr Michael Heller and I always ask myself how did I not switch over sooner. It's hard to find doctors or anyone who you would feel comfortable with your kids. Napoleon Pediatrics are also partnered with Children's Hospital, which makes it even more available.  If you are looking for a pediatrician, give this place a try.

My wife and I are locals, regulars of Locale, and frequent the custom made salad station. Yesterday, it was disappointing. The arugula served was limp and mushy, past its sell-by date, and the individual veggie bins looked as if they had not been changed since the previous evening. This is the 2nd time we've been to a local downtown eatery in the off season to find food that is usually high quality to be sub par. Businesses need to keep their quality consistently high, not just during tourist season. We're your local customers who will keep coming back, but not if we're served sub par ingredients.
Came here on a recommendation one rainy saturday night, and granted I wasn't dressed to the 9's, the host was rude to my husband and I and we never got a table. Not sure I'll ever go back.

After calling this morning,and the restaurant accepting a reservation (so we thought) upon getting the restaurant we learned that they do not accept reservations. After finally being sat we waited 20+ minutes for a server to even stop by. After stopping multiple different servers who all said they would figure it out, we still waited a while to get service and we all ended up going to the bar to get drinks. We ended up having what we believe to be the manager serve us. I'm highly disappointed in the lack of service we got. Our whole table being the the industry understands being busy, running behind, and all other things that can come up. But this was unacceptable.

Really enjoyed my experience here! Great food & customer service. We came in to order to-go food before the beach. I ordered the chicken curry salad with the peanut dressing and ginger lime dressing - so good!! My boyfriend ordered the smoked salmon salad and loved it as well. Everything was fresh! They also gave us tea and soup of the day samples. Can't wait to go back and try the brunch

We were passing through and needed a spot for a couple of nights.  It was New Years Eve weekend (+sugar bowl) so all RV sites we're booked except for a couple in the east.  This was the better of the two we stayed at.  The hookups all worked and the manager was helpful and friendly. 
Three significant challenges:
1. Adjacent to a train yard so we did hear them (bring some soft music to hide the train clanking sounds). 
2. The bathrooms are dated and could be cleaner.  If u have high standards, stay elsewhere.  
3. Everyone warned us to avoid walking in the east; just too dangerous.  

When we called they informed us of the train yard so we knew and were prepared.

I've visited my fair share of salons (East and West coast alike) and never have I come away more satisfied than when I patronize this fine establishment. I've only ever requested Frances, so I can't speak to the other stylists, but if they command even a fraction of her skill I'd recommend them without reservation. I've had cuts ranging from a simple trimming of bangs (which took, incidentally, a mere five minutes and looked exactly as I requested), to giving shape and definition to a formless, tangled mass of chest-length hair, to shearing off several inches of the aforesaid mass to achieve an angled bob effect - all looked, in a word, perfect. Frances has an uncanny ability to look at a photo and reproduce the hairstyle depicted without fail. Before discovering this hidden gem of a salon, I'd never gotten a haircut that I felt looked good straightaway (normally it needs a few weeks to grow out before I grow fond of it), but Perfect Cut has spoiled me in that department. Also, unlike a good number of other stylists I've encountered, Perfect Cut doesn't inundate your hair with handfuls of product/blow-dry it to within an inch of its life before you depart (resulting in a look which, though attractive, is invariably short-lived and impossible to replicate). What you get when you walk out the door is more or less what you'll see the next morning after some time with a hairbrush. 

And need I mention the unbeatable rates? I've had eighty-dollar haircuts that were painfully mediocre compared to the ones I've gotten from Frances for a little over $20 (tip included!) The laid-back, friendly atmosphere and pho next door are certainly pluses as well.
I ordered a filet mignon roast for Christmas Eve. It was delicious and everyone commented on how well it was cooked. I will definitely be back

Amazing coffee at a very reasonable price! I got a Vanilla Latte and a Cappuccino and both were phenomenal. The location is super close to Tower Groove Park and has a cozy sitting area!

I've never tried the food here but looks good and seems reasonably priced.

We are very happy with the Richland animal clinic.  They are the primary care veterinarians for our cat Sage.  They have been able to get in her in quick, and we haven't had any problems.  Sage is as pleased as a cat can be with their services.  We have not used the pet boarding yet just the veterinarians.

Food was delicious, but our server was inattentive and extremely slow. When we first walked in the staff was extremely friendly and welcoming, we were immediately sat at a table with no wait. Our server gave some brief info about the restaurant since it was our first time dining and got our drinks. We ordered the zucca chips (highly recommend) and our entrees. The server did not check on us to see how the chips came out until we were almost finished with them. We noticed all the tables around us got bread, yet we were not offered any. Someone else delivered our entrees and again, we had eaten a decent amount before our server checked in. He did not offer refills or even provide silent service by automatically filling our glasses. I believe a manager standing at the host stand came and refilled our drinks for us. We waited 10 minutes after we were done eating for our server to stop by and offer boxes, and even longer to get the check. The restaurant was not that busy, needs more efficient servers.

The Facebook reviews of this place are harsh AF so I'm glad Yelpers are more realistic about what they expect from a farm. Jeez!!

We spent 4 hours there today for their fall festival. I can't figure out all the complaints people have. Here are my thoughts: 

1. I thought the prices were reasonable. $9.50 for adults, $5 for kids 3-11, and 2-under free. And parking is free!! 

2. Yeah they have some activities that cost extra. Who cares? Most are outside vendors that Sweetfields has come in so, they expect to make some money. $5 pony rides, $5 for face painting, food, pumpkin patch, Apple cider and lemonade (worth every mother effing penny!).  Just bring some extra cash or skip that stuff. 

3. There is way more that you can do for free. They have a lot of animals, a corn maze, hayride, bales of hay, a play house, "play ground," and lots of other games. You could easily come here and not spend another dime. Cornhole, 2 huge tires and 4 bales of hay entertained my 3 year old for nearly an hour. What can I say? We're city folk! ‍

4. It's really well maintained and the staff is super helpful and the animals are well cared for. Also they have clean Port O Pottys. You read that right. CLEAN PORT O POTTYS. I always thought that was an oxymoron but these people pay staff to stand outside of the bathrooms and clean after each use. Not all heroes wear capes. 

5. The food options are good. They had a few food trucks with options like BBQ, pizza, etc. All of it looked good and there was no carnival food. We enjoyed our lunch there before leaving. 

6. Like all fall events in this area, it gets busy. That's just the way it is. But whether you go here or anywhere else you are going to deal with crowds. Floridians rejoice when it is finally "fall" and nothing is going to stop them from heading to pumpkin patches in droves. So don't go or plan accordingly! 

7. Did I mention the lemonade? Oh, I did. Well, I'm mentioning it again because OH.MY.GOD. It was so good! It's pricy but it comes in a mason jar so it just tastes better. GET IT. 

We drove about 60 Miles (one way) to go here and no regrets. It's on our list for next year.
I wanted to like this place but very little selection. I tried the lemon cupcake it was average at best.

Sakura is 5 stars for what it is - an inexpensive Szechuan restaurant that serves Sushi, Thai food, and even more Americanized foods. 

Recommendations:
- Pork soup dumplings (amazing!! skip the wait at Dim Sum Garden if thats all you're going for)
- Scallion pancakes ($3.5) 
- Create your own Hot Pot
- Ma po tofu (vegetarians be aware, there is pork in the sauce)
- Saigon beef
- Pad Thai (yes, pad thai. it's better than Panang and Banana Leaf)

Tips
- BYOB
- great for group dinners
- yelp reservations

Kathleen is wonderful. She made sure I was comfortable and relaxed. Explained each step of what and why it was being done. 
The facility is very clean and cozy. I am so glad I came here. Felt wonderful afterwards, so I purchased a multiple session package. Also, the app they use makes scheduling so easy and convenient. Love this place and Kathleen for all of her help. Already booked my next few appointments. 
Give it a try... you'll be glad you did. I was.
Found this place while heading somewhere else. The food was great and bar has a good selection. Will definitely go back.

Ordered a carry out.  I often times order carry out from other locations, normally the The gal at the hostess stand calls for a server, not this one. She told me to wait in line for the cashier and she would call a server.  So I waited for 3 people to cash out, the cashier called for a server and I waited again,  why the heck the hostess wouldn't call makes no sense, she too was wearing a headset or she could ask any one of them to help me.  

Nonetheless, a man came up took my order and sent me on my way. I should have checked the order before I left as they gave me country ham not sugar cured ham...

At the Grand location - Odd seating set up if you do not get a private table.  You end up sitting next to strangers RIGHT next to you!  The food was ok...but not a lot of food and I was hungry shortly after...I did like the water situation where they bring you a glass bottle to refill your glass...I LOVE WATER!  I wasnt overly impressed...but unique for the crepe experience!

Avoid this place, at all cost!!! They will rip you off with the repair prices and with the cheap parts they use to fix your device. I found out the hard way when I took my phone there to get the screen fixed. I waited for almost a month for the spare parts to arrive, then I waited for 24 hours for the repair, but then I waited another 24hrs when I saw a fault in the parts they used. So not only did I waste my money and time but now my phone doesn't even work like before.

We went for a late lunch. As others have said, the decor is loud and tacky, but the food and service more than overcome this. The portions are very large, and there was attention to detail. I ordered the chicken chimichanga and my wife got the chicken El Meson burrito. Both were excellent as the pulled chicken was very fresh, moist and full of flavor. I would recommend this over almost any Mexican restaraunt intown.

These guys are great!  I had a tear and worn area on the leather driver's seat on my 2004 Honda.  They replaced it and it looks exactly like the rest of the seat.  And my car is 12 years old.  Their price was reasonable, they had it done when promised and they're nice folks.

Great coffee, can't go wrong with La Colombe, but the service and staff at this location were sadly not as great as the coffee. Hardly greeted as I came into the store, and basically had my coffee thrown at me. I will not be going back to this location any time soon.

My wife and I stopped here for a quick dinner before a concert at the Murat Theatre right down the street. We ordered a margarita, chips & queso, and a couple build your own tacos. The chips and queso were good, but I was a little caught off guard for the charge on normal chips and salsa. The tacos were good, as well, but I only got chicken a pretty basic chicken and cheese type taco, so I would've expected there be some more of those items included. The best part was the wait staff. From the waiter to the person dropping off the food. Everyone took great care of us with a smile on their face. The atmosphere of the restaurant is made by the very cool murals on the walls. Overall, I thought the coat was a little high on most items, but the food and drinks were pretty good. Seems like they have a happy hour too that might be better pricing.

Patronized this place several times since it opened hoping that it would improve but we gave up.  Menu is boring, food is mediocre at best, bar drinks are mediocre and wait staff consistently apparently overworked and good attitude deprived.  Sad because it's in a great location, and it has a nice valet service.

I'm definitely a fan of Pat's. There are a zillion pizza places in Delaware County, especially in this area alone. Pat's stands out because they have good pizza and great sandwiches. The rustic sandwiches are the best. The last sandwich I had was their chicken sandwich with red roasted peppers, tomatoes,provolone cheese and dijon sauce on fresh baked foccacia bread. I can go for one right now.
Sea Bass and drinks great, just yum! The bartenders are amazing a for sure must go! They also have live music, nice relaxeing atmosphere.

Very authentic Honduran food . I highly recommend the Baleadas (Flour tortilla with beans and cream) . The restaurant is very clean and they have friendly staff . They need to improve on the decor and time efficiency preparing and providing the food . Food was very tasty but with lack on presentation by been served in dispensable plates .
DONT GO! Even when drunk... Overpriced and just bad. New York New York is right down the road.

Yesterday I saw Dr. Alex....  I typically see him every two weeks for the last month and a half.  I've lost 14lbs so far. 
Yesterday my appt was for 5:00pm.  
I stepped on the scale and I was a pound heavier than the previous visit.  I was very disappointed and frustrated with myself.  I've made all the necessary changes to my diet, calorie intake, zero to extremely low sugar,  low low carbs, no wine or alcohol.  I exercise 6 days a week.  He actually scolded me saying I moved in the wrong direction and I need to improve but not offering any advise and when I asked how, as he was walking out the door, he goes exercise harder.   
Seriously?!? "Exercise harder"  that was the professional advise I got.  
Personally, if you there to get your diet pills then go but if you're actually looking for guidance, don't waste your money.

I would rate this 2.5 stars. The poboy sandwich is ok. Nothing too stellar but nothing too offensive. However, the low ratings are from the jambalaya--a yellow rice dish that came with undercooked rice. You can imagine how gross that tasted. I've been here a few times, and I like that it has personality, but hard rice pellets leaves a diner feeling very unsatisfied!

My Favorite! Thai restaurant in town. Me and my family always love to come here food tastes is so delicious ( take out, delivery, dining) always tastes good not like others. service always awesome. Make us so happy and enjoy. Never disappointed :) thank you Galanga! :)

I hadn't visited a Melting Pot in over a year, until I saw a deal online to get a good amount off of our meal. I know Melting Pot is expensive, so I figured this would be a good time to re-evaluate the experience. 

The food was wonderful! Cheese (Quatro Formaggio), Entree (Fondue Delight - Chicken, Lobster, Steak, Mushroom Ravioli, Shrimp) and Dessert (Snickers Fondue, Yum!) were just delicious. Tip! --- My date and I were able to share a "4 course experience" which most would argue its not enough, but after the cheese and salad, we were already getting full! I will say the salads were pretty small portions, if I were someone with a huge appetite, I might have complained. Also, the portions for the entree were quite small, but again, you're making your own food, and by the time you get to the entree, you're going to be getting full. 

Alex was an exceptional server. He explained everything in fine detail, with an energetic and positive attitude. We asked for his recommendations multiple times, in which we followed, and all were wonderful suggestions - delicious. The manager made a stop by which was a nice touch. The hostess was super helpful and explained the menu very well - very nice and pleasant!

Four stars mainly because this place could be a lot cheaper for the portion size provided, but let it be known the quality of food is very wonderful! If theres anything that keeps me from retuning, it would be the prices - expect to pay at least $50 per person if you're looking to get your own entrees!

For a cheap movie it's a great place. I've been there several times, it kind of reminds me of the theaters used to go to when I was a little kid. The staff is always friendly and concessions is fairly priced. I spent 10 years working at movie theater in my past, so I understand that things don't always get repaired in a timely manner. I've been there many a times before the incident occurred, they always had cops there on the weekends for security. I always felt safe. Movies are generally only a month or so old and from time to time they even show independent (more artsy or foreign) movies. The big thing is you just got to keep in mind it's a two dollar theater, it's not going to like Opry- that's why it's $2.
Good service during our Nerium market party. Ask me why?! Our server, Coleen was top notch!

Over all it's a clean store and they have  a good selection of merchandise.  Although the vendors along the main aisles on each side are annoying.  They chase you down and ask you a billion questions until you reach the point of wanting to leave the store.  One time a woman tried to put lotion on me - which I don't want any stranger invading my space nor touching me.  I hope the management elects not to bring in vendors to bother the customers soon, otherwise I will be forced to go somewhere else.

We have been coming here since my first son was ever born! We were never disappointed
always leave full! And the food is always good, you also have to try there steamed ginger scallion fish, it's the best fish I have ever had, it's good every time, and also the beef fried rice is amazing just put a little bit of soy sauce and it tastes amazing! Also the fried pork dumpling are delicious, it always comes with sauce, and it's nice and plump! Overall this place is the best and has the best fish I have ever had

I should have read the reviews. I waited for over a half hour. Then the woman made me get back in line to fill out a paper that had information I was gonna repeat back anyway. I almost left during the transaction and should have. My package immediately was lost, never delivered and it was definitely on purpose. Fuck these people. They ruin ur day and mishandle your mail on purpose.

Decided to stop in on a whim around noon on a Wednesday.   There was one other customer in the store, about five employees including a manager, waited for about minute and a half at the counter for service, ignored by all five workers.  Took my business elsewhere.

I love the food and atmosphere at South Street. The service has consistently been outstanding and the food delicious. I love the fried green tomatoes. On my most recent visit, we were celebrating a 21st birthday so we wanted to have a drink first upstairs in the "treehouse" bar. We ended up eating up there as well. Great open-air view. The birthday boy ordered the steamed bucket: he couldn't finish it all. The crab was the best I've seen in Nashville, albeit Nashville is far from any ocean. I recommend South Street to all our Music City Pub Crawl guests that are planning to venture into Midtown.  Have only heard positive things so far. Wish they had their own website domain; it's kind of confusing to find them and their menu sometimes.

Bento and the B1281 Bar is tucked into the last block of 3rd Ave South. It's a neat nod to Hawaii. I can't speak to its authenticity as I've never been to Hawaii, but the food is good. I've had the pork belly at lunch with the tempura eggs several times and it's addictive. Delicious...

i got my nails done here after my friend recommended it and i love it i moved from nj and i didn't know of any good places and this one is truly amazing!!! they listen to you and do exactly what you want!! my nails last awhile and look great the whole time

I was in the mood for Chinese food and was near Costco so I thought I would try this place out.  It is located in the strip mall next to the Edwards Theatre on Cole/Overland.  When I walked in, I could tell they took great pride in keeping things clean and nice.  As we were seated they brought out some Egg Drop soup which was very flavorful and very tasty.  We ordered:

1) Ragoons (Average)
2) Chicken Chow Mein(Average)
3) Chicken Fried Rice (Above Average)
4) General Tso's Chicken(Above Average)

They waitress was great and said they were known for their General Tso's Chicken so we included that in our order which did turn out to be the best thing we ordered.  Overall, everything was good and our drinks remained filled and the place was nice and clean.  As we left, we saw a sign that says they do have MSG in their food but they can omit it if asked and can make their food gluten free upon request.  I wish I would have seen that sign on the way in, I wonder how it would have tasted without the MSG.  Overall, average place.  I would be back to try different things if I was in the area and was craving Chinese food.

Beautiful place unfortunately it is run by the government. Just like any government agency they hire people that need to feel important. I was setting up camera gear to take pictures of my nieces family and was harassed by some park police. They said I needed a permit to do professional photography. I'm not a professional photographer. No money was being exchanged. I just happen to have really great camera gear. Obviously the dude needed something to do and was wasting our time.

Food was great,  we got right in with the call ahead.  But super disappointed that we never once got our drinks refilled, water was empty before appetizer, beers and sodas were never offered a refill.  
Despite the disappointing service, food came out fast and delicious.

A real hole in the wall sort of place. The exterior isn't uninviting but it keeps to itself like that cool kid in your anthropology class that you wanna talk to but he's too busy doing cool things. Lucky for me I had a meeting at Fletcher's, so I finally had an excuse to go inside and then I fell in love. While I was waiting in line for the coffee counter customers and employees were happily chatting it up with each other before 8AM. Blew my mind! You definitely get a community feel at Fletcher's. While I was waiting for my drink the barista took the time to ask my name, school, major, etc. I felt he was genuinely interested and that brightened my morning right away! The tables are on your left. I love that there are varied table sizes, so I can spread out while I work. The shop is not too busy, but never dead. It has a pretty constant flow of customers, which provides nice background noise while working. Fletcher's easily jumped to the top of my coffee shop list after my first visit!

Food is good though a bit expensive. My daughter loves the spicy tuna rolls and the shrimp tempura rolls are very good too. Had a couple of rolls that were so so on taste but that may have just been it didn't suit my personal taste. Food is fresh. Love that the ordering can be done online! Just be careful to note if you are ordering a la carte or a full roll. Mistake we made once. Chocolate bubble tea was very good. Hostess who gave us our food was very nice.

I've been to this Second Cup a few times and I like when the tables and chairs aren't right beside each other as with some of the other locations.  When I've met friends here, it wasn't too busy and I didn't feel like I was listening in on others' conversations and that they were listening in on mine.

I like Second Cup for their variety of treats, including their big cookies that are good for sharing and only $2.  The date square and banana bread are also tasty.  As a non coffee drinker, I usually have tea or Italian soda but usually stay there a few hours enjoying good conversation.

If you are in the mood to shop or eat, the location is in Mayfield Common close to many stores and restaurants.

I came by for lunch with my mom on a weekday around noon, and we were quickly seated. Our waiter was friendly, and although we had to wait a little for him to introduce himself and bring us drinks, he was politely apologetic about it. We were still looking at the menu anyway.

I ordered the lunch combo of chicken enchilada soup and a chicken fajita ($8). The soup wasn't too salty, which was good, and I enjoyed it. The fajita came with three tortillas and some toppings. I asked for no guacamole or sour cream, so the waiter offered to give me more of the remaining toppings: cheese, jalapeños, salsa, and pico de gallo. I enjoyed building the fajitas. The chicken was tender and moist, but I felt that most of its flavor came from sauce rather than the grill, which I was a little disappointed about. Also, the onions and peppers with the meat were a little too salty. However, with the fajita built, everything tasted pretty good together. Overall, it made for a very filling meal.

I enjoyed the food and the atmosphere; probably will return when I'm in the area.

This place is just okay to me. Both times, I've come in with larger parties, and the service lacks because of it. 

The food is good, though! I personally find the menu to be a little underwhelming. There are several options like tacos, half chicken, soups, etc. but it makes it hard to really understand the overal concept of the restaurant. And, it's definitely on the pricier side of things.

However, the queso alone makes everything worth it lol. Order it to make all your troubles & worries magically go away.

A few years ago ownership changed and The Holy Ground is now acquired by the same group that owns Bayou Wine & Beer Garden. At first I was skeptical about a new crew and possible changes to prices, but thankfully they realized the value of the existing regulars and that abrupt changes would disrupt the loyalty of their customers. (Pretty sure prices only increased on certain items by only 50 cents.) Since then, they invested in new glassware, gave the place a fresh paint job, added TVs outdoors for sports, added beautifully stained picnic tables, built a GORGEOUS group sized booth and expanded their tap selection. Additionally, the kitchen is now run internally rather than contracted/leased out and the Irish staples like Shepherd's Pie remain. Most importantly they retained their bar manager John L. who not only knows everyone and treats them like family, but gives his blood, sweat and tears to ensure the success of the bar and his staff.

This is by far favorite place for brunch. I go here a lot with girlfriends and do our "boozie brunch". Ask for Rick, he's amazing.  Bring as much champagne as possible! Cheese plates are always awesome, and everything is so reasonable when going for brunch.

Great Cuban sandwich
Steak jalapeño wrap was flavorful and filling

Great Espresso 

Nice spot to sit relax and have a good meal.

Eric B's review and mention of Philly made me HAVE to review this.. esp. since a coworker is about to enter grad school @ UPenn soon... 

Go to this adorable, kickbutt market if ever you're in town to enjoy the sights and history of Philly. Everything that you could possibly think of is here... er, dare I timidly suggest, the Pike Place of the East Coast sans all the fishmongering shows?

One amazing time, trying to thaw by nipping into places intermittently... have gone for a visit to "Brotherly Love" land  in the dead of winter...still, so thoroughly thrilled to have run into the Terminal Market after a visit to the train station (and, of course, to Chinatown!)

Wink; thanks Eric!
The staff was very friendly and my car was nicely cleaned and detailed in a timely manor. Overall a very pleasant experience.
Idk   bout that place they suck the place is nasty rude manager ArAb I think  I heard it wAs FOR sale mmmm save your money we won't be back

Although I am not a fan of the name change (Shinju was so much cooler), they got everything else right.  First FS kept everything good about about the old spot (namely the fresh and innovative sushi) and fixed the things that were holding it back from sushi greatness, namely:
- More tables translates into shorter lines
- More space; tables are further apart (you can still talk to your neighbors, you just don't have to anymore)
- More sushi chefs = less time waiting (and drooling over your neighbors food)

Bottom line: This is the best sushi for your $$$ in Philly!

Don't bother with the "subs" yikes! Like a hotdog bun. No iceberg lettuce and very lil meat and no Italian dressing as I ordered. I wonder if they've ever had an Italian sub at an Italian deli. It seems not. I'm embarrassed for them. I'll stick with the pizza

I don't even like to eat meat and I loved these ribs! The ribs were very meaty and deliciously tender. Also the sweet jane bbq sauce was just right! 
We visited here from Peoria, Illinois specifically because we saw it on Man vs Food. We also met Pappy himself who was kind enough to take a photo with our dad (an avid bbq man) and treated us to a free rib. Thanks Pappy!
My only complaint is the enormously long line. You enter from the back, then follow a snaking line through the small restaurant. Pappy, you have a great business here, go ahead and pump up your size and work staff!
We recommend, call your order in, and pick it up to skip the 60 minute line. Enjoy!
We have meet George from a referral through a friend two years ago.   He is very professional of what he does.  someone you can rely on to run you property smoothly.

I don't know WHAT they put in their cornbread, but whatever it is, like, take all of my money. 

In all seriousness, I love the food here. We happened to stop by their Sunday pop-up in front of Plant Love Ice Cream on Mother's Day and decided to get some black-eyed peas, rice, and cabbage to go. So glad we did. Ray and Casey are wonderful humans.
Ordered the Kelly and the roll was burnt on top. So disappointed by the laziness and lack of care. I love Steins and recommend it to everyone that comes in town. This is such a bummer.

We loved this place.....everything.....the food, the staff, the music....it was all A+.
Make sure you have the chicken stack.  WOW.  The brisket appetizer was excellent too.  Can't recommend it enough!

We were out on date night and things were not going well before we got there.  It was a Wednesday and busy with a singer and people hitting the small dance floor. Honestly, I'm a person who like a quaint and quiet spot, but I know that the Living Room can be upbeat spot. So, we picked a spot in the back and listened to the singer belt out one Beatles tune after another, really nice!!!! Rachel was our server and gave us great recommendations for dinner and drink. We tried the Freakshow Red by the glass, then settled for the Petite Petite by the bottle. Rachel kept things moving and our Black and Blue Nachos arrived promptly. I was really looking forward to a nice steak, but after ordering the ribeye, I was told that they were out of that and the filet. I just chocked it up to the way my day had been going and continued to enjoy my wine. Kate, I believe, was the assistant manager on at the time. She went above and beyond to make up for nothing more than my wanting a steak. I was offered a nice cut of flank steak medium and mushrooms! Then, we were compted our deserts and given drink coupons. Look, I'm not looking for something because things didn't work out, but they really went above and beyond to make our night out end on a high note! I can't thank you enough for everything!!!! See you all again soon.......
Great service, and even better food! Get the big cheese, you won't be disappointed! Live music on the awesome patio, what more could you want from a local restaurant?

This place is a joke. If you have over eight people they charge 18% gratuity automatically. And they will not even split the check eight ways. We waited forever on food and drinks and once we got the food it was nasty. Do not set yourself up for this place. The waitress does not deserve a tip and they do not give you the option! Please do not waste your time and hard earned money here!

Like an Oak tree... in it for the long haul.

Solid choice for breakfast if you're in the area. Decent food. Decent prices. Decent service. Nothing mind blowing. Nothing trendy. Just solid.

My first trip to Johnny's was better than my recent visit.  My husband and I both had the shrimp and oyster PoBoy.  It was strange because the only way I could get that combo was to order a half shrimp and half oyster so I was charged for 4 1/2 sandwiches, however, the priced ended up being about the same if I would have ordered 2 whole sandwiches, I just had to rearrange them so each had some shrimp and some oysters.

Anyhow, the shrimp were very hard (way overcooked) but the oysters were good and of course the french bread was out of this world.  Could have used a little more mayo in the dressing and the fact that they charge you if you want your sandwich dressed is a little strange.  

Will have to try a few other PoBoy restaurants next time I'm in NOLA.  Johnny's isn't bad but it's not great either.
Bone marrow is excellent. Server explained the specials. Good cocktail. Closes at 10pm.

LOVE! LOVE! LOVE! This place is the perfect addition to bring Plant-Based Health and Wellness to the Green Lane area. The juices, smoothies and acai bowls are unique and DELICIOUS and make you feel AMAZING! I love the incorporation and focus that is put on the arts too. From painting classes to barre/tai chi/yoga practices, to essential oils workshops to watching local live bands play acoustic, this cute little shop is providing something for EVERYONE to enjoy :D  The owner, Natalie, is a ray of sunshine that fits perfectly with the island vibes/theme of this adorable little cafe! Everything from the straws to disposable utensils are eco friendly as well which is a huge PLUS!!  I can't wait to see what more is to come! You will NOT be disappointed! 

** PS-  the banana whips (vegan soft serve ice cream) are ridiculously good and the Breakfast Smoothie is my FAVE!! **

Anna,  and Libbey do such wonderful pedicures,  spray tans, lash extensions and waxes!  Feel pampered and comfortable when I'm there. Spa is clean, friendly and affordable.  I've never had a facial but confident it will be perfect when I do.
Seated promptly which is a plus, the resaturant was not busy. My family sat for 20 minutes without having our order taken. I probably will go somewhere else next time. Very disappointing.

Great mall with a lot of good stores.  It is always spotless.  Also, a great Security staff that is very helpful if you need anything.
I was reading through the reviews and I'm just wondering why someone would give the mall a one star rating because they were unhappy with something in Dick's.  They should be posting that on Dick's Sporting Goods.
Nice updated playground for kids to play on.  More ordering lanes added this summer. Happy hour drinks rock!!!

WOW! I'd been hearing about this place since it opened, and finally got the chance to check it out. I ordered the brisket and pulled pork with potato salad and slaw, while my friend had the brisket sandwich Hogwood style with mac and cheese and grits. 

Meat was excellent quality, especially the brisket. The potato salad had a different texture, a cross between regular potato salad and mashed potatoes, while the slaw was super fresh and more like a little side salad. Both incredible. My friend also raved about her meal. 

Hidden gem of Franklin. Will definitely be back!

I had a guest from out-of-town who wanted to go "someplace cool" for Sunday brunch. What the heck do I know? So I looked up brunch on Yelp, saw this place had a solid rating, and off we went.

We arrived at Honey's at around 11am. There was, as expected, a line. It wasn't a big deal. It was gorgeous and sunny outside, there were benches (well, planters with wide edges), and the hostess lowballed the expected time, so we were pleasantly surprised to only wait half the time she stated. Our table was squeezed in between two others, but the noisiness of the place actually provided more privacy than if it had been silent. We set about reading the menu. It was extensive and slightly confusing (they provide you will all the menus, including dinner, although many of the dishes on it can't be ordered before 5pm), but it had a lot of tantalizing options. Pear-Nutella french toast? Brisket sandwich? Chorizo desayuno? I wished I was in a bigger group of people so I could sample more dishes. 

I ordered the chicken-fried steak and eggs, while my friend got the Breakfast Bomb, which is advertised as "a buttermilk pancake stuffed with scrambled eggs and your choice of breakfast meat". We cracked our beers (BYOB) and settled in for a good long wait. And I mean looong. Boy howdy. That food took nearly an hour. 

In the end, the eggs were delicious but the chicken-fried steak was a sad disappointment. I didn't eat more than a couple of bites, as it was overcooked, soggy, and almost totally unseasoned. The Breakfast Bomb was a good choice, though--I tried that and I highly approve. Like a McGriddle but made out of real food.

I would definitely come back again if I was in the neighborhood (and the weather was nice), but I'll stick to traditional breakfast fare from now on.

I was hoping to really like this place and I will say the service was great. Our waitress was very friendly and attentive even on Cinco De Mayo. However the food was not great.  We ordered the guacamole and it was missing something... it just didn't have any flavor. We got the Molcajete and it was just ok. I've had one before at another local Mexican place that was much better. For me, it was a little too spicy - I didn't love the sauce in it.  I will say the Don Julio Margarita was delicious.  I may go back to try something else but there are so many Mexican places I better at this point.

Went here for dinner recently. First off, the restaurant is cash only. There's a bank of america down the street if you need it. Secondly, La Viola Ovest is right across the street from La viola (regular type).. I don't quite get why the owner would want to pay rent on two locations, but that's his decision. La viola Ovest is open on Mondays--I think the decor of LVO is much nicer, with a more open tablescape. The lighting is also much nicer. We went to dinner at around 6 PM, and the restaurant was half full. By the time we left at around 7, it was completely full-- so make reservations if you plan on visiting any time after 6. 

As far as food goes, I was completely satisfied. We ordered the Penne alla caruso ($10), which is a penne pasta in a slightly creamed tomato vodka sauce with peas and pancetta. The pasta was cooked perfectly al dente and the sauce was not overpowering. The pancetta was a bit on the salty in 1 inch chunks, which I wasn't a fan of, but if you like pancetta, you'll like it. We also got a chicken dish ($14) topped with prosciutto, asparagus, and fontina cheese. The chicken was moist and when you got the perfect bite of chicken, asparagus and proscuitto, it was heaven. The dish came in a mild tomato sauce with braised lettuce and potato. 

Overall value is great, as portions were more than adequate with a low price tag. I find that some Italian places have a tendency to provide behemoth amounts of food for a $$$-- which to me, isn't worth it. Instead, LVO allows you to eat like a human and leave with some dignity. The specials sounded really good too, there was a special squid ink pasta dish served with a lobster tail that sounded really good, but again-- I felt weary about getting a dish with "lobster tail," because most places give you a tiny morsel with you guessed it, a 100% markup. 

Ignore my rambling--- try LVO, you'll be pleasantly surprised :)

The food was amazing! Freshly prepared and the best tasting sauce I have had outside of Italy. A variety of moderately priced specials that makes it difficult to decide what to order. This is our new favorite for Italian.

Why 4 stars? Because the atmosphere was fun, and our server was great! While MacDinton's could be just "another bar", it wasn't. I love the Tampa locale as well, but the St. Pete spot was cleaner, less crowded, and less well, stuck-up (which I hate to say, but it is the truth!).

We started at McDinton's before a concert at Jannus, and enjoyed a few happy hour drinks, and a plate of Irish Nachos. The nachos were fine; your standard bar grub. 

We ended up BACK to MacDint's after our concert for more drinks and some Jenga...which was a good time. Again, I just loved the atmosphere and vibe you get in St. Pete.

So I've been coming to this dry cleaner for years. I have to admit I have never had a problem with them that couldn't be resolved. I've been to so many dry cleaners in the past that have ruined clothes and cause me to have the most negative experience and then blame me for my garments for the issues, ultimately caused me more. This family company is totally opposite, they take the initiative and stand by their customer. Time after time I'm greeted by name, with a friendly smile, never forgotten never not thanked for my continued business. Keep up the great work!

The food is great, but the service is lacking. The staff is unwilling to make minor changes to orders. Other than the GM (she's great) the rest of the staff seems unhappy. I've been there several times and this is a common theme.

I love Frenchy's Saltwater Cafe. Been going there for over 25 years. Really good peel n eat shrimp. We like them hot. The onion rings are great as an appetizer. I usually opt for the Frenchy's Saltwater Trio( scallops, shrimp, and grouper). I like the grilled version best. The fried grouper is excellent as well.

Why 5 stars?  Because it's a local champion.

   ---   ---   ---

The best Cuban Sandwich I have had in Tampa.  Hands down.

I know it's a pretty simple sandwich, but I've been on the hunt for my clear cut favorite for years.  The target has now been discovered, I will be a returning customer for a long time.

This place has gone downhill and the pizza that I am currently waiting on will be our last.  We live very close and are waiting nearly an hour and a half.  The quality and reliability have both plummeted recently.  Pizzas show up looking crazy, something in the order is always forgotten.  The last pizza literally looked disheveled, and looked like it had been cut by a drunk, not to mention was crappy.  When I called to check on current pizza 30 minutes ago I was told it was out for delivery, but we literally live so close that we could have walked there in the time we've been waiting.  If it does show up, it will likely be cold.  Cecil Whittakers, here we come.
Food was good. We tried the charred oyster, fresh oyster, gator tail, crawfish pie, jambalaya, gumbo, shrimp and grits. The grits were a bit salty but we finished all of the other dishes.

The pot stickers were extra doughy. Not appetizing at all.  The beef and broccolli was supposed to be extra spicy and actually tasted rather bland. This was a first time last time at the location. 
The staff were very nice during the ordering process.  The store appeared clean.
It took 30 minutes to get my rather small order on a Tuesday night.  $16 for an appetizer and entree.
I won't bash the place, but I won't return either.

I'll begin by saying I love the food at McAlister's and I frequent the location in Fenton, with top notch service and quality food. This visit to Maplewood, however, was just sub par. I walked in before it was too busy. I had my 1.5 year old with me. The girl (who acted like she may have been a manager) took our order and seemed annoyed that my friendly son was trying to talk to her. She also seemed annoyed that I was asking questions about options on the kids menu. I finally settled on something for my son because I didn't want to hold up the line. I asked for no cheese on my spud but it still had cheese, and I thought "oh it was an honest mistake". My son and I enjoyed the food otherwise, but I was disappointed that we sat in our booth (that was only the second one away from the register so very close to the front) for over 30 minutes and not one of the 3 workers came to get empty dishes, refill drinks, or even offer a friendly smile. At one point I started counting how many times they would walk by us without saying anything and it went over 15 times until I stopped counting. I needed to get a bowl for my son's leftovers but since no one could be bothered by us, I had to literally pack up my belongings, pick up my curious boy, and head back up to the counter to ask for a bowl. The guy who was there again seemed annoyed that I would even ask for one. I told him I also needed to place an order to go, which he took. I had to wait for another 7-10 minutes for my order to get ready which meant another 7-10 minutes of my very curious son risking irritating the folks in this fine establishment. One final thing- when I asked the girl from before if my son was supposed to get a cookie with his kids meal, she told me they were out of the mini cookies and told me I could take a big one for him. Well, thanks I guess but don't make this my fault, lady. Perhaps they would just rather have the teenagers and adults whom they were much friendlier to, than a mom and her adorable little boy? 

Either way, I'll continue to frequent McAlister's in Fenton and skip the one in Maplewood.

I am so disappointed with SaladWorks. I went there today for a salad I shouldn't have gotten. They reduced the size of the salad and charged me more!!! I've been going there since it first opened. Now they put it in a bowl and you only get one SCOOP of lettuce!!! I had it as my dinner and it didn't even fill me up!! NEVER GOING THERE AGAIN

Delivery took awhile but it was well worth it. The crust was some of the best I've ever had, and I'm not a huge crust fan. They weren't playing around with extra cheese, it was loaded and delicious. Will definitely get pizza from here again.

We ended up here on a Saturday night per the recommendation of someone who claimed it was the best restaurant in the burbs.  After reading the reviews, my hopes were high for a city-like dining experience out here.  Arugula did a pretty great job! 

We made our reservations day-of via open table and the earliest we could get was 9 PM.  The restaurant was very full when we arrived.  It's cute inside and you can see the kitchen.  Low lighting- nice for a date.  Lots of larger parties there so clearly they accommodate groups.  Arugula does a great job of reminding you that they're a BYOB so bring that wine.

We started out with one of their specials- a soft mozzarella with pesto and tomatoes.  It was so good!  We also ordered the broccoli rabe con salcicca which was amazing.  I was nervous about sweet veal sausage but it was delicious.  I wasn't starving so I ordered the insalata arugula and it was wonderful- loved the hearts of palm.  My dining partner got the pollo capri which he really enjoyed.

Why not 5 stars?  Our server was kind of a jerk.  The food was definitely delicious but it wasn't something that was so good that I'm dying to go back right away.  Is it worth a shot?  Absolutely- especially given other options in the area.  Will we go back?  Definitely- just not right away.

Party of 7 army folks...varying ranks and personalities. So to please everyone at the same time hardly ever happens.  The consensus was there wasn't a bad thing on our table. People were reaching across the table eating off other's plates.  They don't skimp on anything...not taste, not portion size, atmosphere.  We are already planning to return!!!

The pictures on the menu were not what the actual food looked like when I got my food. The general tso chicken was decent but had very few pieces of chicken in it. The Angry Bird St Paul sandwich was mediocre, kind of dry. Glad I was able to try it but will not be back.

Employees here are friendly and ask if you need help. Otherwise, they really just let you shop and don't bother you much after you tell them you're just browsing. The selection here is a goldmine. I've seen Rails, Marc by Marc Jacobs, Joie, Equipment, etc. I've never sold clothing here but I'm sure it's the same as every other Crossroads in that they just give you barely a fraction of the price, but that's the usual. I'd definitely come again just to purchase.
Awesome food and great service.   Carter was an amazing server and would come back for his service alone.  He made the night so much more enjoyable

Met a friend at work for a quick lunch and this was his go to.

The place is really cute; a converted gas station, cinderblock walls, brightly colored with lots of local artwork. Broken up into several small dining spaces kept it intimate.

They approach your table with samples of their featured tea and soup.

Server was sweet but a bit distracted and forgetful.

My friend requested a sandwich which was formerly on the menu and they were happy to oblige.

I've been craving pastrami and went with The Woody - pastrami, Swiss cheese, honey mustard, thousand island, southern slaw and red onion and for my bread I chose the classic seeded rye ($8.99) with a side and I had the soup of the day ( tomato cheddar - creamy and light!).

There are LOTS of interesting sandwiches - in both name and flavor combinations... I need to go back to try some.

A reasonable place to stay, but it is definitely different from other motels/inns. Enjoyed the kitchenette included with every room.

-) Took a really long time to check in with only one person on duty.
-) I was disappointed that they did not include shampoo.
-) I was surprised that nobody was on duty when I wanted to check out.
-) A real negative to me is false or misleading advertising. As you can see from the sign they are advertising WiFi on the sign that you can see from the highway. I did not use it and would not have used it, but was surprised to see that they charged the couple in front of me for it.

On Saturday we went to Peg's for breakfast. We normally go to the one down town, but because we live in Sparks we decided to try them. I ordered corn beef hash and eggs pouched hard and my husband ordered the Mexican breakfast. When our food came to us I right away checked the eggs and they were very running. The waiter took my plate back and had them redo it. When he brought it back the eggs were even more raw than the first time. He signed and took them back again. By the time he got it back to me the other food on the plate was cold. There was a lot of grease on the hash browns and the corn beef  hash was way over cooked. I ate what I could that was edible. I was really surprise at this as we have eaten at the other Peg's and never experience this. The food my husband had was ok and he said he would not eat there again. Needless to say I was very disappointed. I think that the old Peg's is better and this one needs some work.

The seating was fast and the service was OK. Waitress wasn't too friendly and in a rush all the time. No water offered or given. Got Indian me gorang which was not bad but wasn't great, kinda bland. Roti canai was amazing! Must try. Probably wouldn't revisit

A must for local seafood!

I was in town for the weekend and heard from multiple sources that Pesche was not to be missed. I'm a big fan of Butcher and Cochon, so was excited to try the group's spin on seafood. 

My husband and I decided to go for apps and drinks. We did not have a reservation but from other reviews saw that the bar area is first come first serve (and offers the full food menu). We arrived around 7pm on a Saturday and luckily grabbed the last bar seats available (thanks to the hostess who gave us the tip on who was being seated next). The place was already fairly crowded and continued to fill up as the night went on, so we were happy we got a spot. The atmosphere at the bar and the restaurant was very cozy with some cool rustic decor. 

The bartenders were awesome- very attentive and gave solid recommendations. We ordered a half dozen oysters - Local 3 from Louisiana ($1.35/oyster) which were surprisingly very large. We immediately wanted more. The bartender suggested that we add some of the Dauphin Island ($2.75/oyster) to the next order. Those were delicious - very clean and well worth the additional price.  We also got the crab leg small plate (great flavors) and the fried bread with seat salt app (yum!). For drinks we tried some of the gin cocktails and were impressed. Can't speak to the mains, and thus the four as opposed to five star rating, but everything coming out looked amazing.

Overall, great atmosphere, service and food. Next time I'm in town I'll be back to enjoy dinner!
Every time I been there so many people.The food is ok ,The server is so slow.I hope they can serve quick.

I live near downtown Indianapolis and recently began a new job in Carmel. I had become mildly addicted to amazing sandwiches with Pogue's and Wildwood being my go-to's. I had almost given up hope for finding such a shop in Carmel until I read about Joe's. 
I've only been once but my sandwich was delicious! I ordered the IPA Braised Beef and it was perfect. Amazing beef quality and the toppings were subtle and well-placed. The bread was soft and complimented the overall ingredients well. 
Only complaint I have is the value..My sandwich was $9 and much smaller than anything I would have gotten downtown. I understand fully well that local, quality ingredients are going to cost a bit more but I'm accustomed to paying the same amount and getting chips or soup and a drink with a much larger sandwich. It'd be nice if they could work out a sandwich combo or something similar to give you a little more value for your money.

I used to enjoy treating here.  The last few days I called because I was having a non-stop migraine.  I followed up three times since I received no call back and each time I was told that they would provide an URGENT message to my doctor and still almost 3 days later I received no call.  DO NOT under any circumstances use any neurologists from this place because apparently they do not have any regard for their patients.

We loved it. I highly recommend it for people who are adventurous and looking for something out of ordinary. 

It was a delight to the palate with fresh local ingredients that deliver a heathy meal without feeling overstuffed

Vegan dishes along with beef will make sure all your guests dietary preferences are met
