99% of the time, this location is excellent! Have had some trouble ordering on the app and getting my order at the time that is "promised," but it won't stop me from going back. If it happens, going up to the counter gets the problem solved very quickly. I came in after an interview once, and the manager comp'd my lunch! Great staff.
We went for strawberry picking, and instead, we got so much more! Vegetable picking, snacks from the grocery story and sat outside listening to live music! Wonderful morning! We'll be back!

Yes, this bookstore has an incredible selection of art and architecture books, and it's practically bursting at the seams, which makes for a fun afternoon of browsing.  Unfortunately, I've always been put off by the staff, who are often unhelpful, unfriendly, or generally holier-than-thou if asked a question.  This place is worth stopping by if you're in the Rittenhouse area, but if you're making a destination trip to an independent bookstore, I would always choose Headhouse Books in Society Hill over this.

We live in Monticello, IN, and the heating and air conditioning contractors in town are limited.  We didn't have a problem getting 3 to 4 companies to come out to our house and review the work we needed done, but getting them to get back to us with a quote was nearly impossible.  ARS was prompt to come take a look and give us a quote in a timely manner.  The first quote was severely underestimated which was good for us, but it was so low and unfair to them that we let them give us a second quote.  Again, they mistakenly set the quote too low, but they were willing to honor it so we went ahead and hired them.

We needed a new furnace, extensive new duct work snaking through the low pitched attic, new intake and return vents in every room and the old furnace moved to the garage and installed with a new gas line running from the house to the garage.  Most companies weren't willing to do that much work, and some wanted us to get a subcontractor to dig the gas line.  ARS did it all for under $7,000.00 (including the price of the new, Amana, top-of-the-line, energy efficient, furnace which cost $4,500.00) which was at least $3,000.00 less than anyone else.  Little did they know that our ceiling had at 5 layers and one of them was metal.  They broke three saw blades cutting holes to install the vents, and I'm sure it took 5 times as long.  It took two guys 2.5 days to finish everything.  If they didn't lose money doing this job, I'd be shocked.

Now for the complaints.  They did not put tarps in any of the rooms when they cut through the ceiling so we had drywall chunks and dust everywhere covering everything, including our beds and carpeting.  They did not put tarps on the floor so we have muddy footprints on all the floors and carpeting.  If we had known they weren't going to cover anything, we would have done it ourselves.  They hand dug the gas line from the house to the garage and hit a cable while doing so.  We could see that they had frayed the cable, but instead of telling us or fixing it, they tried to bury it again with dirt.  After they were done, we noticed that two of the vents weren't blowing air properly.  We crawled into the attic and found that they hadn't attached the duct to the vents securely so we went around and did all that.  Our ducts are super noisy when the heater kicks on.  We're trying to figure out what the problem is with the dampers since adjusting them hasn't helped.

In summary, we got what we paid for and we may have even gotten a bargain.  We did get a guarantee that says we can call them, if we're not satisfied with their work, and they will come out and fix the problem.  We have an amazing warranty on the furnance.  The project manager was knowledgable, personable and came out to check on the project twice.  I'm sure we weren't a priority, and the guys were probably told to rush the job which is why we have some slight problems, but we'd hire them again at that price.

Ordered to go through doordash. Whomever packs the food has no care in the world. Missing items and wrong items in place of others. This is not the first time I have had my breakfast thwarted by inconvienence when I pay extra for said convienence from this establishment. I gave you another chance after months of pretending you didn't exist and you botched another one, left me with remorse of paying almost $50 for what looks worse than waffle house.
Good coffee but the interior isn't that cozy, it's more just people at their laptops working.

Today was the actual opening day for this Tampa location of Kruk's Philly Steaks and I was fortunate to be one of their last customers of the evening.

First of all, I appreciate a hot sandwich shop being open this late as their 10pm nightly closing is clearly posted on the door.

The store looks simple and without clutter featuring the blue and red colors of Kruk's longtime team. I was familiar with this space from the previous sub shop tenant and Kruk's makes better use of the space.

Employees were terrific to me, answering my questions about the store and a couple specific menu items that were new to me like "broccoli rabe."

My "Pepper Cheesesteak" featuring sweet peppers and wiz (I also added tomato at no upcharge) was made fast. Both the meat and bread definitely had the flavor and texture of an authentic philly steak sandwich. 

Next time, I will ask to go slightly heavier on the wiz because I want to taste more of that signature ingredient.

Because it was Kruk's "Opening Day," an appropriate term for a place featuring the name of a longtime major baseball player, all sandwiches were just $5.

Even though Kruk's is brand new to Tampa, the first store opened two years ago and there are now six locations from here to Naples.

I'm told John Kruk should be making an personal appearance at an official grand opening here in the near future.

Not only will he talk about the restaurant, but you will want to hear his story about facing Randy Johnson in the All-Star Game at Camden Yards. It was one of the funniest All-Star Game moments in baseball history and helped make Kruk one of the more likable guys in the game.

My wife & I have been going to this restaurant for at least 20 years. We've never found a better steak. The service is impeccable. Sometimes we'll eat at the bar & enjoy the company if the bartender, where we get the wonderful cheese & crackers with our cocktails.

I tried Hellas for the first time and it was pretty good! I ordered the gyros (pronounced "yeeros") platter and for about $11 it came a/ a small Greek salad, pita triangles, gyro meat, tzatziki sauce, seasoned green beans, and your choice of potato or rice. Sounds like a lot of food but it was very well portioned -- it was truly a platter. 

The food was good, but I've had gyros before and they tasted the same so there wasn't anything special. 

It's kind of a hole in the wall place -- it wasn't busy and there was only one waitress working. I would venture to guess there are other Greek restaurants in the area w/ better Greek food + a more modern ambiance -- it felt like I was on the "Big Fat Greek wedding" set. A bit hokey in my opinion!

I think this place is famous for its chili grill oyster and lots of piggy plates. We ordered the chili oyster which is great, and duck gumbo which is exceptional. We also ordered LA cochon and bbq rib, the cochon is good however the rib is kind too strong for us (the source)

Was hoping this place would have done a better job. I decided to get the powder dipped nails like I always do. First off, there were only about 10 to 15 colors to pick from. Secondly, the job they did was absolutely terrible. The process they did was wrong so my nails turned out to be lumpy with lines through them. The shapes of my nails weren't even close to even. I was honestly shocked at how bad of a job they did. I immediately left and went to my other nail salon and thank goodness they re did them. Also, the service was okay. The lady was nice, but stopped working on my nails 3-4 separate times to answer the phone, talk to walk-ins, schedule other appointments, and take care of other people which honestly started to annoy me. I wouldn't ever go back!

THE GUAC is amazing..they make it fresh at your table!  I have a little warning if you order shrimp fajitas(they are good)  it runs around 25 or so bucks but chicken or steak are a normal price.  The fish special is also secretly expensive- just ask for the price before you order the special.  I haven't had everything on the menu but so far everything I've had is soooo good.  Def try this place!!

I live about a block away so I'm biased, but I think its pretty damn good. No frills, its a neighborhood pizza shop, but its good, italian style like that guy said. Not too thick, not too thin, good balance in the ingredients.
Very poor lumber selections. The lumber that was there was horrible! I've seen better lumber in a dumpster.

Now closed. They just shut the doors, disconnected the phone and left no information about what happened. Those who had deposits for events are SOOOO stuck. 
Go through open table and you get this message: Permanently Closed - 39 West American Bistro

Stopped in the other day with my husband & 2 kids & got the following, which I highly recommend you try!
~The Polli - Fresh Chicken Cutlet, Fresh Mozzarella, Prosciutto di Parma, Shaved Parmesan & EVOO
~The Tiny - Fresh Chicken Cutlet, Fresh Mozzarella, Roasted Red Peppers, EVVO, Shaved Parmesan & smeared with our Basil Pesto
~Pizza Steak with Mozzarella
~Small plain pizza
The sandwiches are stuffed so much you can barely fit your mouth on it to take a bite!  You can tell the chicken cutlet is made fresh there.  The sandwiches were amazing!  I only ate half & saved the other half for lunch the next day.  The pizza here is so good too.
And although it was a bit pricey, you get what you pay for & this was definitely worth what we paid.  Keep doing what you're doing over there guys!

These guys are great. I've brought my bike to them every time something goes wrong with mine. They cover a lot of different repairs and at a relatively cheap cost. I recommend that you upgrade the tubing in your tire because of all the thorns and glass. What is best about them is that they are up to date on all traffic laws and will give you the equipment you need to ensure you comply.

Long, long ago (February 29th thru March 1st 2020) in a park far far away (Julian B. Lane Riverfront in downtown Tampa) there was the 50th Annual Gasparilla Festival of the Arts. Before a pandemic forced us all to socially distance, a large group of us arrived at the beautiful park on the river by bike, automobile, or water taxi. We spread across the massive lawn  of Julian B. Lane and listened to live music, ate from local food trucks, and walked around and feasted our eyes on rows and rows of unique art from over 250 artists. 

Couples and families relaxed on their blankets on the well manicured lawn. A tent was set up with tables and chairs so that we could eat our delicious food, watch the band perform, and get some reprieve from the hot a** Florida sun! There were some excellent food options by the way including Dolce Dough, Taco Lady from St Pete, and Wicked Oak BBQ.

This festival was a great way to spend the day with your family and friends. I can't wait until we can all get together like this again.  Until then,  stay home, stay safe, and stay well.   :-*

Excellent spot!  Extremely knowledgeable staff.  It's a must visit place.    Very unique to find a place that has their own delivery service and these guys are the best!  I highly recommend this place
Totally worth it if you can afford it. My appointment was on time they did an incredible job. Will definitely be going back!

This place is incredible! If you have any interest in raptors (eagles, hawks, and condors) you must go here! These guys are taking care of a segment of the planet and are doing wonderful things. The specimens they have in the cages are unbelieveable! This place is so worth your time!

Embarrassing. Sukhothai was closed so needed to find another Thai restaurant open on Mondays to treat friends from out of town. Looked at reviews and picked Bangkok. Not sure what others were eating ---certainly not what I had!
Will never go back.

i first took Bolt   bus the first time In Nyc in last Oct in Nyc  to Boston had a  very good   experience the   driver was dick  we had Boarding passes he wont let us on till later but he let people on whom paid him we finally got on the Bolt was very comfortable ride they have comfortable leather seats wi fi service so i   give it 4 stars MEGA bUS

I was super psyched for my first bike ride of the season when suddenly I heard a pop when pumping up my front tire. I wasn't going to let a flat get in my way so dragged my bike down to Philadelphia Bikesmith. 

They were able to look at my bike right away and the cost to fix the tire was only $7. The whole process took about 20-30 minutes.  They also took a look at my back tire and pumped it while I was there. 

In the end of the day I have no complaints about the result of the work, but there were a few things that rubbed me the wrong way.

First, the girl working on my bike took a phone call while working on my bike and joked about it to the person on the other end of the call and in the others in shop. I'm all for double-tasking, but that just made me a little nervous since my safety was at hand. Maybe this happens all the time at shops everywhere. I just didn't like that it was happening right in front of me. 

She also took the liberty to grease my chains without permission. This took my total bill up to $12. If she asked me I most likely would have authorized this work since my safety was at stake, but she absolutely should have asked me before doing this. 

She was very nice and gave me some tips on how to pump since it's been a while and I'm still sort of new to my bike. I just wasn't thrilled with everything that went down during my visit. At least I was able to get a quick fix and get out on the road in the same day.

***Edit: I did misunderstand the pricing structure. I was accurately charged and can now appreciate the complimentary lubing. However, at the time of my visit, Sarah did not appear to be working on anything or drop what she was doing to fix my flat. At the time I entered the store, she was sitting at the front register. I can't speak to what she had been doing prior to that. Secondly, while my bike was in the stand, she was still working on it while on the phone. My concern wasn't that my bike would be dropped, it was that her attention was split. Maybe that was her 10,000th tire fix and she can change them in her sleep, but that won't take away the nervous feeling I got during my visit.

Average pho.  Not near as good as pho grand, mai lee, or truc lam.  Guy that took my order is grouchy.  Unfriendly. He said he doesnt have tap water instead buy water.  What kind of restaurant that doesnt offer tap water??!

Best Shrimp Creole!

It's divey and townie feeling even though it's crammed with tourists.  Service is efficient if not terribly friendly.

If you're not used to NOLA bathrooms, these might squick you out.

This place is great. The food is consistently good, the portions are great, and the prices aren't outrageous. It's become the standard that we compare sushi restaurants to, as everywhere else we go is a disappointment compared to what we get at wasabi.
Hidden gem in far bucks county. Clean and modern decor. The options are endless and everything has great flavor and was fresh. Great lunch specials.
If laying on your bed squirming in pain like u just drank bad water in India, don't eat the numbing hot pot

The history cruise was awesome. You got to experience the mighty Mississippi River see the sights and learn about the history of the city. The tour of the battle of New Orleans was interesting.  The best parts was on the way back our history guide Charles have talked about Katrina. Talk sells it short. It was more like a one man theater show. By then end I had tears in my eyes listening to his description of the events that took place. The boat tour was worth it but his performance made the day.

Yas, queen. It lives up to the hype. Visiting and tired of the same cajun and creole foods everywhere? Grab some modern eats that includes fresh vegetables. Great atmosphere even though it's always packed. Recommend, son!
Daniel is AMAZING! I love what he did to my hair especially since he was fixing someone else's mistake! I already made my next appointment!!!

My friends and I were on vacation and heard great things about this place. I nervously ordered Chicken Saint Charles, with my egg fried hard, without the sauce and with a side of Breakfast potatoes. The potatoes were ehhh but the Chicken Saint Charles was amazinggggg! I'd go here again if ever in New Orleans and had time to spare.

The wait to be seated was A LOT! In the time that we waited we were all able to buy things at the gift shop and change our flights home (during hurricane season) and there was 10 of us!
The wait to get the food was even worse!!! Damn near passed out before getting it. Because the food was good we didn't complain but it is what made me take a star off.

Over priced wings. Taste good but price doesn't match the ambience. We sat at an extremely tilted picnic table that appeared dirty but may have been cleaned, stains just can't be removed. Not really the place for me.

Dr Maxwell is an excellent doctor and his staff is consistently helpful, friendly and professional. Like many other reviews have mentioned Dr Maxwell takes time to listen to you and makes you feel valued. He is very through in describing your test/ lab results as well as explaining different treatment paths and why he thinks one path is the best. 

Recently I was out in a new medication and when I started having negative side effects I was able to message Dr Maxwell through their patient portal and he messaged me back the same day and had a new prescription ready for me soon after that. I can't recommend Dr Maxwell high enough!!!

First of all let me just say that I will never enter this Walgreens again even if zombies attack and it is the last place in the world for either safety or a cure. Staff here are rude and obnoxious mouth breathers. Went in for simple over the counter meds (which I got and went to pay for) and the cashiers acted as if they owed the place making snide stupid comments. Go any place else for your needs... Trust me you will be better off.

We had the Ruben and fries excellent , and they had the latest Crown- Apple... I have been around visiting some of the Tampa's area and Cherrys get's a big thumbs up for the food , price, and it's clean a even bigger deal to me.....we will be back often...

Loved this quirky coffee shop. The coffee and treats were good and the staff was engaging and personable. My niece and I stopped by and found out it was open mic night, so we stayed. We loved the variety of personalities and musical styles and the interaction from the crowd. If I lived in Eagle, this would be my hangout.

We LOVE this place!!! It really is a hole in the wall and parking is kinda tight but don't let that deter you.

When we find ourselves in Tampa and in the mood for empanadas, we immediately think of Antojitos. The chicken empanadas are my favorite but the stuffed yucca is also on the top of my list.  Get some pan de bono too!

Service is great even though they're always packed. Prices are cheap.  The food is flavorful. 

Every table is given some SUPER SPICY sauce that looks like a homemade salsa. Be careful (if you're not conditioned to spicy Latin food) or your tongue might fall off!! But seriously, it's got some flavorful HEAT!

This place is a class act! The beer and sours were awesome! I was looking for cider and they didn't have any but the owner offered sours and gave me several tastes until I found one I liked! So friendly! And the atmosphere is super nice. They also have a fun patio area with games. I will definitely go back!
Great family owned business.. made me feel right at home! Thanks Max with u on the team.. my baby is in good hands

Wow. I have been here five times now, each time it gets more impressive. The food quality is unmatched. The Habanero Kreeper salsa is to die for! Loved the queso and the ability to customize it. Hongos Tacos are my personal favorite but all the tacos are tasty! Exceptional service. Korrie, the General Manager, goes out of her way to make sure everyone is taken care of. Great decor, atmosphere and food. What more could you want?!

The hotel itself is updated and very clean. The pool area is very nice with a large hot tub. The staff has also been pleasant and the breakfast had a lot of great options. WiFi had issues at first but kicked in and was fine overall. Water pressure isn't the best.

Also, the hotel is very close to the interstate and if you get a room that faces it, you will hear every car that goes by. If that bothers you then be mindful of it. I had a harder time sleeping/relaxing due to this. It's also pretty tricky just to get to the hotel due to a very awkward intersection. 

One good note on the location though, is that there is a family fun center right down the road that has great putt putt so that was a little bonus for this side of town.

The prices are reasonable, portions good sized, and the soul food here is great! It could use a bit more spicy, but it is always fresh and cooked well.  The chicken and fish are fried well and very tasty. I love that they offer so many sides. I love their collard greens most. They are tender and not overcooked. As I said, the food could be seasoned more, but  I just add some of my own powdered spice blend at home. Their yams are not overly sweet and for many that is a good thing. Honestly, we've been happy every time we ate from this establishment. 
The staff is polite too and that is what matters to me most. I'd rather eat at a less than perfect, but good place, if they have good customer service, than a place with perfect food but horrible customer service. I can't stand establishments that act like they're doing you a favor for taking your money. Appreciating your customers is the way to success not just good food or product. So, definitely check them out.  You won't be disappointed

Bookmarked Cafe Amelie before visiting New Orleans-especially after seeing pics of the Doberge cake. It did not disappoint! The food was scrumptious. The ambiance was beautiful. We started with the goat cheese and fig appetizer-yum! I had the special pasta of the day- chicken penne, and my sister had the shrimp and grits. Both were delicious. I was so stuffed at the end of the meal, so I asked the waitress to box me a piece of that delicious cake. She included some plastic cutlery after I explained that we were staying at a hotel. Ate the cake later that evening, and it was as delicious as it looked in the pics. Cafe Amelie is a must when visiting New Orleans!

I have been wanting to venture over to Garrison since their opening and last night I finally made it! My friends and I made the short walk from Sparkman's Warf and found ourselves here to play some virtual golf.  Little did we know how much fun we were actually going to have. I'm not much of a golfer but I did love that you can switch it to games like zombie dodgeball.

When we ordered drinks I was even happier, my old fashioned was perfect and not overly sweet like most bars make it.  The poutine was soooooo good and perfect for the for of us to split. To top everything off our waitress was very friendly. Overall really happy with our experience and look forward to coming back.

Ps. If you dont want to walk from Channelside just take the trolly!
Been all over Florida and this is the best Cuban Sandwich I've had. Simple, quick and very reasonably priced.
Armando was thorough completing all of the service and maintenance required.  R & R communicated regularly using phone, text and/or email as required.
If you can stand the 35 minute wait, the food and service will be great.  I would suggest the cheeseburger in paradise and a cold draft beer..  Amazing......

Bella Nashville seems like a good place for my 1000th review on Yelp.

I didn't get to fully enjoy the pizza, as I wasn't feeling well, but i still thoroughly enjoyed the couple pieces of margherita that I tasted.  The meat looked even better.

They make all their ingredients fresh, and then cook it in a big wood-fired oven right in front of you.  

The staff is pretty friendly.  They need a better notification system than just yelling and hoping you're standing nearby when you pie is done.

Wow SO GOOD!!! The staff is very friendly and the fish is very fresh. I had the sushi sashimi platter and it was excellent. It had Cobia, escolar, tuna, shrimp and salmon and they were all super fresh. A little more about the staff--They are so nice! Restaurants have had it very tough the last 13 months and many have become a little rude or worse. So it's very nice to come here and be treated with genuine kindness and hospitality. 
Very highly recommend

I wanted to like this place when we stepped in and it was a small little diner. The food we ordered was good and everything the guy grilling was making looked good however... the service . We walked in with no acknowledgement at all. We sat at the little bar stool area right next to the waiter and still nothing. We weren't even given menus... so we had to ask the lady next to us to see hers. Eventually the waiter asked for our drinks which all we got was water & it sat on the counter while he complained to the guy cooking about another table. After he just dropped our waters, he didn't even ask if we were ready to order. He went to the back, came back with silverware & started putting that away. We had to tell him that we were ready to order which when we did, he told us to give him a second. Finally, we got our food and when we did, we just asked for to go boxes because we were just over the whole situation. 

Hopefully, if you decide to go you'll get better service.

They make you wait thirty minutes even if you have a reservation. They don't tell you they are out of something and offer you a substitute. They just figure you're an idiot, give you something else, hope you don't notice, and then argue with you when you do. The food takes over an hour to come out. The food was decent, but nothing great for how craptastic the service was.
Very nice workers and clean love the room service.  Love the price. I thank them for helping us.I will come back and stay. Very clean.

Typical Hampton, they're just ok, and they usually do the job.  I had points and was looking for 2 queens, free breakfast and something close to U of A.  i got 2 out of 3.  it's not very close to U of A, but it's also not that far either.  it was a good 15 minute drive.  My boy will likely attend U of A and i likely won't stay at this place due to distance.  I will say Saturday night we stayed at Fairfield Inn(Marriott) in Phoenix and it was way better (cleaner, upgraded, etc...) but more expensive.

Had the 4 in 1 tour yesterday at 5pm with Josh. It was 2 hour long, walking around the area and stopping at landmarks where Josh told stories. Josh was amazing as a host; funny, very enthusiastic and had a perfect tone of voice! Even when I was far away from him I was still able to hear what he was saying. Very important to not block walkways for others passing by. Also, very important to tip your tour guide at the end because they do make your time worth it!

I went here for the first time this week for a pedi. Anita is really nice! I got a regular pedi (not spa) for 20, which at first i was scared at the price, but it was worth it. Anita took her time and gave a REALLY long massage. 

just remember: it's cash only, but luckily one can run to TJ's across the street if one needs to.

Cute decor and menus seem to be actual Tucson newspaper articles from the 50's.

Service was shaky, but should settle down soon. Despite being brand new and super-busy, we got our meals very quickly.

HUGE portions. 

The side salads were crisp and green. Brother's pecan crusted trout was fine, SIL's "cheeseburger" salad was gigantic, my tri-tip was hard to chew. The mashed potatoes and steamed vegetables were good, as were the potato salad and cornbread. The cole slaw was just cabbage and mayonnaise. 

There were three hot sauces on the table. "Baby Burn" was plenty hot.

Service: service was decent, and it was busy yesterday and the restaurant was full but they manage to keep up. They replace the grill when it turns black right away. Some other KBBQ gives you butter to grease the grill and make sure the grill doesn't burn or the meat doesn't stick but they don't. Not a big deal as the fat from the pork belly is a lot of grease.

Food: selection was ample and the meat are very generous. The marinade and flavor of the meat is good. The only thing I didn't see is selection of sauces. They have only two types of sauces peanut sauce and sesame sauce. Other KBBQ have sauce station that you can to grab sauces like hoisin sauce, sriracha sauce, soy sauce, chili, etc.
Great food BUT don't sit on the balcony, sun was unbearable, ruined a wonderful meal and night out.
Went in today for the first time with my family!!..It's a little pricey but the food was great!!...

We stayed here this week. It was our first time to Santa Barbara which was a great trip. This motel was clean, great location, reasonable prices and very friendly staff. Not only did they let us check in early when we arrived, they let us check out late when we left. Flowers were gorgeous! We will be back!
Funny family style steak house. Excellent service but mostly excellent steaks and sides. Will return whenever we're in the area.
My favorite hair salon in Nahville. Staff are super nice and love the atmosphere. Most importantly, best hair cut!

Food quite good, tried several items, but the service was horrible. Sat at a table inside where I was looking over the outside area where I seen the other customers getting much better service, I noticed in my section other patrons looking for their server also.

I came into Lux to get a full set for a wedding I was in. I had a certain design in mind and even called ahead so I could be convenient for the employees. I left with nails that only lasted a little under two weeks. The design was okay but not how I really wanted. The nails were uneven and had ripples throughout them. I was very unhappy and will not be returning.

Chicken pesto pizza was amazing 
Staff were a little uptight and it took a while because they forgot us but I'd go back for the taste.

Extremely dissapointed.
Sales exec (Jeff) came to our home, took measurements and showed us some pictures online to choose from. This was at the beginning of the COVID outbreak so we appreciated being able to choose a product from home. Jeff was helpful, polite and we were able to select a product and purchase our doors that day. We signed a contract and put 1/2 down. 

About 12 weeks later, the windows arrived and were ready for install. 
Install was scheulded in a timely manner and two lovely men by the names of Adam and Ryan came out two days in a row to get our new sliding glass doors installed. We purchased five panels in total, suffice it to say, it was an expensive venture and we were excited.

Unfortunately, once installed, the locks/handles on the doors literally would not work. We could not get in or out of our home. My strong husband, the two installation experts and myself struggled for more than ten minutes with each handle. The installation folks told us that they were "genuinely surprised we had ordered these handles as they typically don't work and are not popular....". We were, of course shocked. Why on earth would anyone sell us something that didn't work? I called the store to speak to the sales manager and explained what was going on. I calmly explained that I would not be paying the balance of the invoice until I could actually operate my doors. He asked me "who was your sales rep?", "did you come into the store"?.....Of course I didn't come into the store we were in a quarantine and as I'm not an idiot I wouldn't have spent thousands and thousands of dollars on doors that don't work. Four days later the manager and one of the sales folks come out to the house to "fix" the handles. They basically removed them and soddered them down so that they would open and close properly. There was no apology. There was no offer to compensate for our trouble. I asked if we could please have different handles and was told if we wanted different handles we would need to buy completely new (three thousand dollar doors). 

I was told by the installation techs that if we review they get a bonus. I want to reiterate they did nothing wrong so Ryan and Adam deserve that bonus! As for Jesse, Dave and the sales exec that I never saw again.....they need to learn how to run a business. Do not make the mistake that we did and avoid this company. Doors and windows in FL are expensive and these types of investements should be treated as carefully as the customers.

I literally purchase 90% of my produce from the Nashville Farmer's Market because the quality is fantastic, prices will save you money, and you support local farmers all in the same swoop!

This is my juicing headquarters and I try to visit a couple of times a week if possible.
It's only 2:36am  and your restaurant closes at 3 am that's pure BS. We just paid a $13 cab ride to come to your restaurant and you turn as away at 2:39am.

The spring rolls were good, the pork baboons were good but that one piece of mini cucumber did not give the crunch factor. The pork chashu ramen was a lukewarm, tepid broth. I'm not sure what the red strands were in the broth but by golly they were bitter.  I asked for spicy chili oil on the side....$1.50 extra...I didn't know I paid extra until I looked at the receipt! It's not the money but the principle

When you are craving homemade Indian food that's quick, this is the spot to be! I was hungry and the food was quite quick. The food is flavorful and spicy! So if you can't handle spice , heads up let them know before ya order so they can customize it. Great spot and flavorful inexpensive Indian food:) btw the deserts are eggless and amazing!

Absolutely love this place! Such a classic diner. Everything is super clean and service is friendly/efficient. 

We came for breakfast today, and everything is exactly what they should be. My husband had mainline special plus muffin. I had bagel with lox and cream cheese. When they say jumbo bagel, they didn't lie. 

I plan to come back for lunch or dinner soon!

We had a great food and dine in experience! They were amazing and helpful to our family! Food tasted fresh and great! Love it here and will always come back! They have a kids place and great clean potty rooms!

Brought my car here to get it detailed after my friend got sick in the passenger seat. My car was not very dirty at all other than that. Paid $100 for the interior shampoo. After having my car for three hours I was expecting my car to be nice and clean... Boy was I disappointed. I immediately pointed out to the guy that my car still smelled like Puke and did not have a hint of shampoo smell at all. I also pointed out the smears on the windows along with the dirt all over the body of the car. They directed me to drive my car back through the car wash. I did then while they were redrying my car I requested the manager. I pointed out the chunks of Puke in the floor of the car. They were claiming they shampooed everything yet nothing was damp and it didn't even look like it had been vacuumed! The manager agreed, he took my car and attempted to reshampoo my car in 10 minutes which resulted in my passenger window control being broken. I went from being unhappy to livid!! I demanded to talk to whoever was higher than him immediately. The manager called his boss on the phone and I told him everything that had happened. He apologized immensely and asked me to bring my car back in the morning. He even offered to pick my car up at my work if need be! The next morning I drop off my car again and the man I spoke with on the phone was there. He personally hand washed, shampooed, and waxed my car. When I came to pick it up he gave me $100 in free car washes to make up for what I had gone through. 

This car wash made a mistake by not doing a good job on my car. Yet when confronted with the issue the main manager did not hesitate to fix what was wrong and to do all he could to make it right.

Sage diner was an awesome experience. We were seated immediately and had an awesome server. You must order the freshly squeezed OJ for starters. Their biscuits and gravy was perfect..I'm from Arizona and I find east coast rarely has it. Sister ordered the stuffed French toast which was delicious as well. I would recommend getting extra cream cheese sauce on the side since the actual French toast isn't stuffed. Everyone at the table was completely satisfied. Hope to make it back here during another trip!

Can you say, YUM! 
This place was so delicious from the food to the drinks!!  I'm not familiar with cocktail names bc I don't indulge often, so I asked the bartender for a suggestion.  He prepped me an Amaretta Sour, and ...it's definitely going to be a go to drink for me from now on.  I just hope the hubby can make it like he did  The burger was seasoned perfectly!  The cauliflower bites were tender and fresh.  The wings...oh, the wings...so flavorful and crisp.  The service was top notch as well.  
If we are ever in St Louis again, we will be back!

Always some of he best in New Orleans!!!!
Ya gotta try all the ones Chef Ron has on his menu.    Never gotten any bad food from here.

I have 3 boys ages 2, 3 and 4 and The Indy Zoo is one of our absolute favorite places.  This is a beautiful zoo.  The landscaping is always so well kept and there are lots of nice places to sit and enjoy a snack or rest (good for young kids).  There are also 2 new playgrounds that my boys love.  You can tell the animals are well cared for here. We love to see the macques (swimming monkeys!), pet the sharks (super unique for a zoo), & feed the birds.  Tons of interactive exhibits!  Be sure to bring your stroller though because stroller rental is $10 even if you have a membership.  Can't wait to spend more time here with summer right around the corner :)

Hands down this is the best spa in town! Everything about this place is wonderful...the soothing waiting room with great little snacks, the warm foot soak I enjoyed while sipping champagne and the life changing Swedish massage that I received from Sara. At one point it felt like she was massaging warm butter into my back...wow! The entire place smells fantastic and their boutique has some great little pick up gifts. I will be coming back here and bringing friends!

A great winter spot here in Edmonton, especially when you're lucky to sit by the fireplace.
Great crowd, great atmosphere! Real unique drink selection too. Have always been treated really well by the staff there.
Great people and food, They always have smile on their face , curbside or dine in. I found this place to have the best hotdogs in town.
Orgasmic!!! Love this place!! If you are ever in the morthen part of tucson and wanting some great mediterranean food then Pita Jungle is the way to go!!! You canr beat great prices and great food!!

Um Hello! Who doesn't love Chipotle! Honestly the best go to place around. Being able to indulge in some of your favorite Mexican eats is always a Todd thing. 
My go to is. Chicken bowl with extra chicken. Brown and white rice. Pinto beans. Hot and mild red salsa. Corn salsa. Sour cream and cheese. Then chips to add that special something. It usually takes me 2 days to eat my whole bowl. Love it all every time.

Terrible service from people working thursday 10/28 . UNDER NEW MANAGMENT. The new menu is not updated on their website or on eat street. Staff only agreed to refund $2 dollars for an incorrect item if i would wait until after closing hours  and wait for staff delivery drive to pick up an incorrect side of vegetables from my home as proof. i have been a visitor of this restaurant for over 20 years and never have i been treated so rudely and straight up insulted. The "same" items are definately not the same. If you are a vegetarian watch out.. all the veggies have been change. 

I would give zero if I could.

Went during the week. Not a lot of people. Awesome animals! The girls loved it! Wish the staff would be more involved with the kids like teaching them something. Green bags for the barn yards are a dollar each.

Loved this place!  The ambiacne is so cool and the food amazing.  Went for my birthday and was pleasantly surprised at how wonderful it was.  The bar was quirky and cute.  Our waiter was a riot and took great care of us.  The blue cheese dressing on the salad was delicous and the steaks had a great crust and taste.  Felt is was cost was resonable for what we received and cannot wait to go back!

We ordered the bundle at this place. Included pizza and salad. Both were good. However the killer were the garlic knots. I don't know what they put in these things but if it's the only thing you ever order from this restaurant you'll be happy.

The service here was phenomenal.  Although the hotel itself was a little above average, the service made the stay worth it.  The staff was friendly and helpful throughout the entire stay. The location of the hotel was great as well because it is right off the highway and easily accessible.  I highly recommend this hotel.

The customer service is fantastic! 

The drivers know the city and are true professionals and I love the lady (Sharon) who answers the phone in the morning. Full disclosure-I've left my home twice since March 19th. Both times for medical appointments. One day I took four taxis and on another day I took two. All six times I called 215-666-6666 and a nice lady (Sharon) answered my calls. By the sound of her voice it's the same nice lady and she always treats me with kindness and dignity. She's very re-assuring and I've to admit that this pandemic has turned me into a nervous person who is easily rattled by what I've seen on the two occasions I've left home. The only place outside my home I felt safe was in this taxi services' cabs which are clean, sanitized and all of the drivers wear masks.

I know I just told you that the taxis are clean but they really are and they send a text message when they arrive and everyone is kind and patient. 

What more could you want?
Wowzer.   Bring your mother and your children for a lasting memory of the greatest dive bar on the planet

We had the omakase. Go somewhere else. I learned the hard way that there's no such thing as "budget omakase," that is good. And we certainly got much less than what we paid for. 

(1) Food:Chef was sick. He kept wiping his nose on his hands while he was making our sushi. It was disgusting.
(2) Food: Sushi / sashimi pieces were very small. We had to eat another meal after (somewhere else). Also, they gave us kind of an odd selection of fish, which makes one wonder if they serve whatever is the cheapest catch of the day.
(3) Service: We asked for soy sauce. They refused to give it to us because they said that they put it on the fish themselves. I prefer traditional sushi, so this wasn't great.
(4) Advice: There were no other customers. There's no reason to make a reservation on Resy. (They charge you $30 per person for canceling if you don't cancel with more than 24 hour notice.) 
(5) Service: When we didn't want to eat something, the chef kept yelling at us to eat it. I personally don't like this level of personalized attention at a restaurant. Also, I think he tries to tell you what they are serving, but the person's English & Japanese is not great, so it's impossible to know what they are serving. Maybe if you speak Chinese, then you might have a better experience?
(6) The "vibe" is not good. 

Bill:
There are also two surprises when you get the bill at the end. (1) They charge you $5 for fresh wasabi (without telling you that they will at any point in the meal or on the menu). Wasabi should be included in the price. This is disingenuous. (2) They ask you to pay in cash and offer a small discount (5%?)
Very bad & disgusting food. Ended up sick & having food poisoning. Never felt as bad as I did the past 2 days. Nothing but constant diarrhea & throwing up.
Brussels sprouts, sweet potatoes, Korean ribeye. You can quit there, but everything else I tasted was excellent as well. This is a mouth watering menu!!!

I recently came back to the spa and this time for a massage on a Monday. Let me tell you they have definitely stepped it up. First they have a spa attendant, she did mention she was new and works m-f so I'm not sure about the weekends. She was very attentive and offered me a tour and showed me to my locker as well as instructions on how to work the lock. Each locker had slippers and robes which was a major issue last time I came and then I was shown to the area for my massage. After my massage the spa host had tons of fresh berries and fruits for the guest. Triple thumbs up and I saw she was bringing in bottles of champagne which I believe you can purchase but I'm alwAys down for some bubbly. So the reason for only 4 stars, my massage while amazing ran a little short partly because I didn't realize they opened 30 mins before the opening time on the door of 9.So I showed up and 8:58 which my massage didn't end up starting until 9:07 with me changing and filling out paperwork. I did go down around 8:25 but didn't see anyone inside so rather than wait I went back to my room. Ok I guess I should have figured it out before, but the masseuse ended the massage at 9:53 which I assume a 60 min deep tissue massage starting at 9 should end at 10 so I got shorted the 7 mins in the beginning and the 7 mins at the end. I was a little disappointed because it felt amazing but regardless I will be coming back and good job GSR for stepping it up. I'm excited to enjoy some champagne and fresh fruit on my next visit.

Went apple picking here yesterday mostly because everywhere else that I was researching didn't have apple picking anymore.. I thought I waited too long and missed my chance.. I found solebury online and made an hour drive and it was amazing! It's in a super cute area and everything is organized perfectly. They have a cute shop that they sell apple donuts ., butter, chips , cider..  their donuts are way above average!  It wasn't very crowded at all either so I think I will try to go again next year at the same time! Oh also their apples are very fairly priced compared to what I saw at other places.. they don't make you pay for the bags.
I friggin love the ban chan (spelling) that comes for free with each meal. dol-sot-bibimbop for lunch is best damn meal for like $9

Friendly staff, wasn't crowded, sat at bar, service good. Now for the rest of the story. 

1. If you have a website, keep it updated! Website touted "Sunday Game Day Drink Specials, $2.95 pints of Miller Lite & $5 ANY shot", when we asked about it the bartender was unaware of any Sunday Drink Specials...football season only maybe (?) although the website didn't say so & we had just come from a Tampa Bay Rays game. 

2. If you list what is on the food on the menu, make it the way it says! I ordered the Low Carb Burger, no bun ( they don't have any gluten free options they are sure of) it stated it was served on a bed of lettuce & tomato with a balsamic dressing & topped with grilled mushrooms, grilled onions & provolone. It came out topped with those items as well as grilled green & red peppers. There was no lettuce & tomato. When I asked about it they did offer to take it back & make a new one. I asked them to just bring me the lettuce & tomato on the side which they did, I took the peppers off. My husband ordered the Patty Melt which also stated grilled onions & cheese. There were no onions, he said it was the worst Patty Melt he'd ever had; his only positive statement was "at least the bread wasn't drowned in butter before they toasted it so it wasn't too greasy". 

This was our second visit. The first was good enough to try it again...maybe they do better when they are under pressure as it was crowded on our first visit. We won't go for a third try.

Music was great! The moon shake was good and the service was great.. but I ordered the fish and chips. The fish was fried so you can't mess that up, right? Wrong... It tasted like dirt. The coleslaw was tasteless. It was just really disappointing. :(

Over 200 reviews, and a 5 star composite, not 4 1/2 stars. That's impressive. This is tough. I waited too long to do the review. I've forgotten too many details. The place was packed. Fortunately we had  reservations. After a couple minutes we were seated, and treated like family. The service was flawless over the evening. The wine was well priced. The food excellent, but I'm not going to be able to give details. I'm not quite sure what local Basque food actually is, but this was good. There is a whole region South of I-84 and North of I-80 across Nevada and Idaho where Basque's have done sheep herding going back to the old West. This is the best of the Basque places I've been to. The only thing missing is the classic drink of the American Basque. A Picon Punch.

One thing's for sure. when you see a Basque place, make an effort to go. Especially for Epi's. It's the best thing near Boise.

I went here for a special date night. The food was divine! We started with a Caesar salad and tomato soup. Then ended with spaghetti with fresh basil. The service was excellent. They push in our chairs for us and constantly checked up on us. I felt really special. I would recommend this place to anyone that wants a fancy dining experience :)

Love this place! Every time I go in to get my cat his food and treats, the employees there always remember me and ask how my wild little man is doing. They have also ordered a case of his food for me before so I don't have to take every can of it off of the shelves which was so helpful. I have also gotten some dog treats and toys for my brothers dog and they have recommended things! Very sweet and informative staff here, even though I moved slightly further away, I will always make the trek back here!

So I learned the difference between a hoagie and a sandwich. I guess I'm a sandwich guy (and it's cheaper... winning!!!). The (cheesesteak) sandwich was HOT and delicious! The girl was also fluent in Italian and reassured me of the PROPER pronunciation of "minestrone" soup!! I would give 5 stars, but the online ordering is a bit challenging due to some misspelling of things on the website causing confusion for the cooks. Other than that the food is just fine especially being in what appears to be quite a secluded area!

Seriously though, we were here twice the same night!  Everything we had was great. Though I wasn't a big fan of the brussel sprouts because they weren't cooked enough for me they were fresh like everything made here. We had many different things and couldn't write about them all but we found coming early and making reservations help. Only thing was service was a bit slow but not too bad for a busy place. We will be back

Pretty funny place.  Basically you pay to get treated like crap while you drink or eat a meal.  The food is good.  Loud music.  Nice atmosphere.  Tourist attraction for those visiting Nashville.  Dick's is kid friendly.  I had a good time. The food was decent.  Nice portions.  A little pricey.  But you are paying for the entertainment.  Service is funny.  They threw straws and mayonaise packs at me. Ignored me.  Mess with the kids wrap them to a chair. It's a cool place.

  Or just hit the bar and get drunk.

First off, the price is right. Other than that a let down! They are pet friendly which is cool but, allowing two dogs to bark like crazy next door to us for hours really sucks! Not the cleanest place! Pool was closed on labor day weekend! And I had a weird encounter at 8:30 am with the front desk. Something tells me they need to upgrade there computer system!
Parx casino is a great place to visit on a weekend. There's always lots of great events and lots of great restaurants.

Great spot for brunch. Wait can be long, especially on the weekend, but worth that time. Their eggs benedict dishes are very good; bacon is very savory; and the variety of options on the menu have been a hit with everyone we've taken there. May be my new favorite spot for brunch in Tucson!

I came here for lunch and having been here in the past and everything was always great we decided it would be good to come back. But today was not like the other days, it seemed they were off point today. I don't know what was going on, I ordered the Turkey bacon ranch wrap, it was soggy and there was NO bacon or ranch at all, as well the fries were hard like they were old. family ordered the chicken fried steak which she said was very overcooked and burnt almost. both of our food was terrible. I was surprised because usually Joey B's has been good in the past but not not today. I was disappointed honestly.

Despite not being a giant monument, which we all know is the epitome of historical research without which no one knows what happened ever, this museum manages to be truly excellent. When I saw this was a building with exhibits based on archival research, artifacts presented with historical context, and top notch audiovisual displays, I was disappointed. How will I learn anything, I wondered, without a giant statue of a rando army dude erected 80 years after the war's conclusion, charging on top of a big metal horsey with a descriptive plaque that barely constitutes a comprehensive sentence? Surely one cannot learn history without looking into the deep stone cold eyes of a dead general with a powerful nickname like "Psycho Wolf" or "Battle Stallion." However, this museum proves that you don't need monuments to remember facts. What a relief! I can finally stop erecting statues for every item on my grocery list. 

Seriously though, the professionals in charge of this new museum deserve an enormous hand. This is how you do present a truly inclusive history. There is a separate exhibit just on the Native Americans and their decision making process as to who to support in the revolution. This is in addition to Native Americans being mentioned throughout the museum. Lots of attention is paid to the role of African Americans, including an in depth discussion of the idea of slavery and how it fits (and doesn't fit) with the equality touted by the revolutionary colonists. I loved hearing about black loyalists and the British effort to ignore the stipulation in the treaty to return runaway slaves and instead resettle black loyalists in Nova Scotia. I would love to see a more in depth exhibit on that humanitarian effort, maybe in collaboration with some Canadian institutions. What I particularly liked about this approach is it didn't simply focus on the American point of view. Almost half of the exhibits approached the revolution from a British point of view, telling stories from loyalist colonists, British soldiers, Hessian mercenaries, and British officials. I really loved that in some of the interactive displays an effort was made to show HOW we can actually know some of the information, especially since many of those involved left no personal written record (also, no monuments). 

We were told to not miss the film on Washington's tent, but honestly, this was by far the least interesting part of the museum, especially since you couldn't really see the tent of get close to it. It was almost have made more sense to have a recreation tent you could physically walk through after the movie. Don't believe the hype, the tent movie isn't that great, and here's basically all you need to know:
The tent symbolizes that Washington, unlike other generals of his time, wanted to be seen as "one of the common people" so he pitched his tent out in field with his troops. Of course, his tent was enormous and luxurious by comparison. By modern camping standards, it's like at least an 8-person tent, and a regular solider tent be smaller than your average 2-person dome tent. But, he was out there in the cold with everyone else, so soldiers trusted him, and that trust continued with his cult of personality into his presidency and beyond. Washington died, his tent was passed onto Martha, and then eventually her grandaughter, Mary Custis Lee, wife of Robert E. Lee (of statue fame). After the Civil War, she sold the tent to a collector to pay for relief for confederate widows. Eventually the tent made it's way to the museum. The End. I now saved you 15 minutes. 

So, all in all, excellent museum, despite the lack of monuments, and Washington's Tent is fine, you can totally miss it and not lose anything in your life.
A very  dependable place for me to go to when all else is closed. Open 24/7. Most elaborate drink selection with soft drinks from all over the world.

This neighborhood pub is fairly new to Tampa Palms area and the name is unique so you know we had to try it. We came in on a Friday night and it was busy, but not overly busy. They have a pretty good size craft beer menu with some solid offerings I haven't seen in other similar pubs. I ordered a porter and some wings from a very friendly waitress and my wife ordered a wrap.  Everything was great, the service was awesome, the food came out quick and the wings were some of the best I've had in this area.

EJD is not the best way to experience football.  First, football stadiums should be open air.  I would even settle for retractable, but closed roof is no fun.  I was at a game yesterday on a beautiful sunny fall day, and it would have greatly enhanced the experience.  Since Green Bay, Mizzou and many others have this, I don't think we can use weather as an excuse! 
Security getting in is tight, and I think they overdo it a bit.  Closing down the major streets around the dome and cops everywhere?  Bomb sniffing dogs, clear purses, and handheld wands?  Maybe this is the wave of the future, but it seems over the top for a regular season game.  The additional security slows entry into the dome quite a bit, so be sure to plan enough time to accommodate this if you want to see kick off.  
Once in, the structure is pretty basic and utilitarian. Little to no character or special design.  It is well marked and easy to navigate, so getting to your seat is easy.  
Concessions are pricey, but no worse than other similar venues.  Offerings are pretty standard snacks and beverages like beer, soda, popcorn, pretzels, nachos, etc.  Beer is beer, so that was fine, but mostly just AB products are offered.  The food leaves a lot to be desired.  Low quality salty or sugary junk food, without many fresh-made or upgrade options.  
The sound and lighting systems are also sub-par.  You can barely hear what is going on and there is always just a lot of overall "white noise" that reverberates around the building (which would be helped by the above mentioned open air setup).  The lighting is similar to a casino- tons of LED, flashing lights, and bright colors.  I don't know how the players concentrate, and it was tough for me.  As I am typing this, it sounds crazy to me, but I prefer to watch a game at a bar or even at home where I can better control my surroundings, clearly see each play, and hear what is going on as it happens.  It's never a good sign when we are at the game in good seats, but have to watch instant replays on the big screen every time to understand what is happening right in front of us!
Very nice lady that was able to help us very quickly. We had an indoor unit, very clean.

The customer service and attention to the clients is superb!! I love going to Kits and everything there is so amazing. If you need a basic tee or a fancy cocktail dress, they have it! The employees are very welcoming and know how to style you in any outfit!!

Horrible treatment to customers, staff member was honest but owner was a complete a**hole. Was going in for a quote on a muffler and resonator delete for a 2001 bmw 325i, and when I asked the owner for the price he said me and my younger brother looked like "rich boys" and that he'd have to charge $600!!! When I told the staff member what had happened he said the owner "probably had to pay off his hookers" and that "his price was extremely unreasonable" even too him. Other than that the place was a complete dump and I would never leave my car to those guys. I dont know how they have 4.5 stars they must fabricate reviews everyday to make up for all the real reviews. If I could give negative stars I would.

I tried the rib sandwich platter for lunch and it did not disappoint. Very tender and flavorful sandwich paired perfectly with asiago cheese, spicy BBQ sauce and fresh bread. I will be going back to try the ribs on the bone.
Great local non-chain pizza place. Love their salads and wings too.  Ask about the specials there is always a good deal to be had. Definitely my go to pizza place.

I've been trying to eat my way around the world here.  Quesadillas aren't quite enough food for me, a wrap is just right, and "chos" aka nachos I typically need a to go box.  Very clean store, consistent food, and friendly service.  I think the Far East dishes are a little plain, My favorites are the Pangea (feeds 2), the buffalo wrap, and Thai Peanut, but I've enjoyed nearly the entire menu at some point.

I am staying at Parc St. Charles. I was told by three different people that this hotel is in a prime location. I agree 100%. I was able to walk to the french quarter in just minutes. If necessary there are several street cars that run in this area. This hotel has a great combination of proximity and distance to the boisterous, fun loving crowd on Burboun St. The staff is very friendly, the rooms are clean, the price is right. My only complaint would be the room temperature. I'm not quite sure the thermostat understands degrees.

I don't usually love Mexican cuisines, but the item I ordered (pictured, beer battered redfish tacos) was delicious.  The redfish pieces in the tacos were large and fried to crispy perfection in beer batter.  The colorful garnish included avocado, Mango salsa, cilantro, and a purple slaw. The decorative sauce was actually a creamy Chipotle sauce that added extra zing to the tacos.  This restaurant had pleasant decor with a Day of the Dead vibe too. Yummy causal eatery!

They have cool decorations, but their food wasn't the greatest. I would say that it wasn't good at all. I went there lured by their $8 lunch special and to only see a couple of trays that weren't even warm. To top it off, my nephew said that he saw them serve us Kern's guava juice, which by the way cost me $3.95. I was really upset. What made it worse was that it gave me a stomach ache. It's a cafe/store, but they have really should make an effort in their food or just make it a store.

Very disappointing and very expensive for what we received.  I had read a number of mixed reviews of Somerset, but the photos and menu were intriguing enough to warrant a try.  The restaurant was indeed beautiful, but the praise stops there.  Our friend ordered a vodka cranberry and we were told that there was no cranberry juice.  Really?  In a fully stocked bar?  It took us 20 minutes to get our first drink order and the food service was no better.  The food was okay, but nothing to rave about.  The drinking water was so undrinkable that we had to order bottled water.  To the management of Somerset - you have a beautiful venue, but get your act together if you want to survive in this competitive market.

The food is decent. However, my friend ordered chicken wings and the and the bag was drenched in buffalo sauce. It was an absolute mess and nightmare to clean. I ordered a side of honey mustard and they should've just said no. They have the tiny packs of kens honey mustard. Anyone who loves honey mustard knows this is unacceptable. The food it's self isn't bad buuuut I won't order here again

Reserved Corks for a milestone birthday party with 30+ friends. Maddie and Ben were amazing!  BEST BIRTHDAY EVER!! Unsurpassed level of service and willingness to do whatever they could to ensure the party was a success.  I highly recommend for that special occasion you may have coming up. 
 Or just for a glass, a flight or a pint any day!

Delicious!!! They were packed when we got there, but they put a couple tables together for our group of 6. The owner came by several times to talk with us and make sure the food was good. Our waitress was also great! We got incredible garlic bread before our meal and my shrimp scampi was rockin! My coworker got oysters and she ate them faster than I could say oyster.
Will be back next time I'm in New Orelans!!!

It was crunch time - slept too late, had a 945 walking tour, and no time for brunch at the hotel. What to do? Rousses Market to my rescue! The overall market looks like a wine enthusiasts dream come true, but they also had warm sausage, biscuit and eggs in to go boxes. The sausage and biscuit (didn't try the egg) were warm and well cooked - the biscuit was flaky without getting flakes everywhere. The cashiers were also very friendly. A great place for French Quarter breakfast on the run.
A perfect start to my weekend in New Orleans. Really enjoyed the live jazz music while sampling all sorts of food off the buffet.
Nice place, authentic enough and delish! Ordered the chicken kabob and they were very mildly spiced, not overwhelming, and most importantly, clean.

One of the nicest restaurants in town, the staff is very friendly and attentive. The pasta dishes are always fresh and very good, especially the bolognese.  We have had the salt baked branzino and it is one of the best fish dishes I have ever had.

Margaret Delcolle is absolutely wonderful.  This was my first time buying a home and at our first meeting she spent almost two hours with me walking me through the process step by step and discussing with me what my needs were.  Every time we met up to look at houses she had  everything planned out, with properties I was interested in as well as some she felt would also meet my needs.  It wasn't very long before i was in my first home!!!  I had worked with a couple of real estate agents prior to Margaret being referred to me and none of them went to the lengths she did to make sure i got everything i was wanting.  Two big thumbs up for Margaret!!

A zoo... that's free?  I was really confused when I walked in and the friendly face at the information desk asked me if I needed help with anything as opposed to a credit card.  I mean come on!  St. Louis just does so many things right.  You want sea lions?! They have them.  You want elephants?! They have them too.  Well I could keep going, but my only point is, this isn't the largest zoo, but they have a wealth of animals and plants with origins all over the world. 

My favorite part of this zoo is definitely the penguin and puffin exhibit.  When you enter the cove of the penguins, you'll experience the heartwarming surprise that can only be experienced when you've had a penguin shake water onto your face.  The bird house is also spectacular.  

The zoo is divided into different zones, and maps are plentiful to guide you on your trek.  I've been a few times, and appreciate the warmth of the staff, and the chance to see the animals.  Okay so I've been to a few exhibits, where theres a little sign that reminds me of the computer with the thermometer indicating an unhealthy animal, but what does that show, but a zoo that values the health and well being of their animals.  

Parking on our visit was $10, and affords you footbridge access in, or you can street park for free as other's have mentioned.  I was wearing a pedometer, and from the spot we got, we walked about 1/3 mile from our spot to the entrance.  Not too shabby. 

Gift shop is chock full of swag.  If you need a penguin shot glass with my name on it, they've got it, but hey they probably have yours too :) 

A must see Forest Park treasure.

Wow, after going to this place for years in its old location in Drexel HIll I came to the new location in Havertown one day,  what a horrible , horrible change. The old location was awesome, 
the staff was knowledgeable  and friendly  the new place must be under new ownership because , allegedly this  location has a bunch of Rude,  dismissive  slack jawed buffoons that seem to care little about customer service . 
Man what a bummer, I loved the old place in Drexel hill.   I will never shop here again.  These guys will be out of business soon, sad, I hate going to Home depot.

I have been going to Kolb Nails for quite a few years. Very small shop, nothing fancy, but I LOVE the service (and the employees)! Everyone is so friendly and you never feel like a stranger even if it's your first time there.The pedicures are great (love the massaging chairs). I always have the technician put a little "design" on the big toenails after I get them painted and it's always something different and it's perfect! The prices are reasonable and my nails (both toes and hands) always last a long time!

Eaten here several times. Market is interesting, but the food / restaurant in the back of the market is wonderful! Nice selection of veg meals, and generally 10 minutes you are out the door. 
Meal prices are very reasonable, and the cashier is always willing to suggest something different - and I have been pleased every time. Keep coming back!

A Face Book open question...
what can be done to get updates from the Service Department? They only respond when they have to be pushed to answer questions about my 2019 Jeep Vin KD158729
I have spoken to Jarrett -service manager 
Lew Asst. Service manager, and 
Lynette in charge of customer care.
None have called to keep me in the loop.
Forgot one thing.  They said they would.
Yes Jarrett sent an email as to parts on order after I sent him two emails for answers.
Each has failed in Customer service one O one
Each have made promises they have not kept.
My Jeep has been at Reedman Toll since Oct 10 today Nov.  11 a month and 1 day.
They have not responded to Kristine at Nation Customer Service.  Kristine stated she contacted Adam area manager who has not responded to her as of Friday Nov 9th.  Kristine at National customer service hands are tied.
She has been pleasant and does all she can.

What a fun little breakfast/lunch spot on the outside streets of the French Quarter of New Orleans.   This place had been recommended to us by the hotel staff.    It was the next block down, so very convenient for us. 

We were greeted by a pleasant hostess whom asked us for our vaccination cards to ensure a safe environment for us all.  We were promptly seated and our server Norman was with us within minutes. 

Norman was delightful and very helpful to us!  We asked a dozen questions and he was for very polite in answering all of them for us. 

We ordered a Orange Mimosa and Peach Bellini along with fried green tomatoes, side of corn beef hash, and BBQ shrimp and grits.
 
Oh my goodness, those fried green tomatoes were out of this world! They were top with Lettuce, tomatoes,  fresh bacon bits, and their special sauce!  I can't even begin to tell you how fabulous they were. 

My husband had the bbq shrimp and grits and said the flavor was savory and absolutely devine.  The biscuit was super light and not dry or dense. 

The service from Norman was top notch and super professional. 

We are staying in the French Quarter for a week and we will surely be back again!

I'd always heard great things about this place so my boyfriend and I had to try it. The Skinny Migas is very tasty. I loved the chipotle sauce and tortilla strips with it. Their biscuits are pretty good too. My boyfriend however, was not a fan of his Corned Beef Bennie. The Ruby Slipper is known for their Eggs Benedict so you'd think it'd be out of this world. Overall I'd say this place is okay. I've definitely been to better brunch places in New Orleans.

Where do I start!!!? I decided to try this place out because I heard "good things" about it and it was a BUST. The food is sub-par and it's over priced for the portions you get. $13 for 4 extremely sour dolmades!!! OUTRAGEOUS. I didn't even order anything else after because that alone was horrendous. And no I'm not exaggerating. It was actually some of the worst grape leaves I've ever had in my life.
If you want good authentic dolmades (grape leaves) go to Tarpon Springs where the Greek food is authentic without breaking the bank or look it up on google because your cooking couldn't be any worse than this place.

I had had an wonderful meal at Park Cafe sometime before I officially moved to Nashville a little over two years ago and then yesterday, my husband (then boyfriend) and I decided to celebrate the happy occasion of Monday by going back for a nice meal. Being that it was a Monday, reservations were definitely not needed. We sat outdoors next to the stone fountain in their new(?) patio area and although it was a little chilly and a little difficult to imagine that you are not sitting in a former parking lot, it was for lack of better descriptive terms, nice.

Pros: The side of green chili mac 'n' cheese was hands-down dope. I would almost recommend ordering two of these and calling it an entree. But then you'd have to order a side of two other entrees because the scallops and the duck that we ordered were also done quite well. The gnocchi that the duck sits on melts in your mouth. We also ordered the special appetizer, mussels. What was remarkable was that each mussel was served with its own sprinkling of ground up chorizo, tomato, and some thick, but delicate green sauce (sorry, don't remember the details of this one). Service was warm and pleasant. And at the end of the night, my husband asked, "How is it that I lived across the street for a year and never came here to drink alone?"

Cons: You have to walk through a bunch of BMWs to get to the front door.

This is my second cigar bar that I have been to in the city. The first one was Niki blanes which I loved, but I'm always looking to try something new so this was a good place to do so!
Just located up on 82nd street next to the old Joe's Crab Shack you can find blend. 
It's very open, spacious and has interesting decorations!
The back is the humidor so you go in to pick out your cigar and then you can sit at a table or at the bar to get a drink.
Very friendly staff! I was impressed at the time they took to answer questions or just make conversation.
 Can't have a cigar without a good drink! I'm a seasonal drinker so I tend to stick with the lighter liquors during these months.
One of the tastiest martinis I've had in a long time! Delicious gin with blue cheese stuffed olives, can't be beat!

charisma/ rizza/ pink lady, most awesome conversationalist I've ever experienced at a club. Musician, comedian, held my attention for more than 2+ hours. 2 lap dances, well worth it. Amazing entertainer, beyond professional, easily the sexiest, down to earth woman in the building. Would come back just for her, any day of the week. Here from Hawaii, and she has been a highlight of Nashville. Coming from a former hustler club bouncer.

After all the photos of beautiful slices of cakes on my Instagram feed, I had to try this place out!

Ambiance: The atmosphere is very cute. There is a bar area and then there is a more sit and dine area on the second level. The available games to play with other people are a nice touch to be more casual and interactive. The dim lighting and seating yourself policy also contributes to the casual feel of the place.

Food: To be quite honest, I was underwhelmed by the desserts. I have been at the Bakery Bar twice and had tried 3 cake slices between those two cakes. The cakes look gorgeous, beautifully crafted with each layer separated. There are also many options and the options change on a daily basis, which is a definite plus. However, the taste for all the cakes I have tried (Cinnamon Toast Crunch, Confetti, Carrot Cake) were all okay. There was not anything particularly great about the taste. It was moderately moist and sweet and had the flavoring of the cake. That was pretty much it. I felt the cake batter could have been made from any other mid-level bakery. The cake slices definitely seemed to be more picture-worthy than palate-satisfying. Likewise, I had order a cake layered creme brulee. Again, the cake seemed to be quite normal and average, taking away from the taste of the creme brulee.

Service: I did not sit at the bar either times I was there but I can say that the waiter/waitress service for the tables are timely and efficient. The moment we sat down, a waiter or waitress would come and greet us, hand us our menus, and pour water into glasses. We had to order cakes and cake pops at a little area next to the bar but there was a separate menu for additional dess9ert. Orders were taken quickly and processed efficiently. Cake slices were also brought to our table at a timely pace.

Final thoughts: Overall, the environment is a nice and quaint, casual space. The food was underwhelming for its beautiful look but the service was timely and efficient.
Excellent fluffy omelet. Best potatoes I've ever had by a wide margin. Great atmosphere. I will be back!

I cannot under any circumstances recommend that you buy a used car from this place. If you do, please be very, very careful. I bought a 2006 BMW 650i and after a short while I realized that it smoked a lot after idling (like a huge puff of smoke). I took it to a BMW specialist, who told me that it is a known problem with the model and that it involved the valve stem seals, which need to be changed. This is a $4200 job at the specialist and about $7-8000 at BMW. In other words a huge repair on top of what I already paid for a car, that they said had been through a 60 point inspection, which clearly was useless.

I thought I was safe, since The Great Britains offered a warranty of the power train. So of course I assumed that the valves would be covered as they are clearly part of the power train. They are not. In fact the warranty they offer is useless. It only covers parts that don't break. Like the cylinder or pistons. These will never break unless you operate the car without oil in it, in which case the warranty is void anyways. 

In short the warranty covers none of the parts that will break on your car. I spoke with a shop who also had issues with this warranty company. He agreed that it is not worth the paper it is written on.

So, I contacted George Weldon of The Great Britains and told him of the issue. I asked if there was any way The Great Britains would be able to assist me with the repair since they had sold me a defect car. They basically told me: tough luck. There has been absolutely zero assistance or flexibility on their part.

I am very disappointed and now I have to pay $4200 for a repair on a car I just bought from them.. So like I said i can not recommend them at all! The fact that they sell a car with a defect shows their incompetence, that their warranty is good for nothing, shows their cynicism and the fact that they are not willing to help out at all after this shows their complete lack of customer service.
