They give used car sellers a bad name!

Oh dear. Was so looking forward to my Friday night Bun. Sadly, it was not to be.
iPho, we were so pleased to see you land in our neighborhood. Vietnamese food! In Fairmount!  We wanted to support your arrival in Fairmount.  But we were so disappointed by the reception on our first visit, we decided to leave before ordering.
Basic customer service was seriously lacking. 101 for a restaurant host is to smile, greet the customer warmly and provide them with some helpful info (or better yet, a table!). Do not leave them flailing by the door, and then shove them on the window counter, when there is space for at least another 8 people at tables (because you haven't figured out how to separate two tables for 2).  The hostess was neither friendly, nor did she seem to have a clue.
Once seated at the window, we were told that it would be a 30 min wait to throw together a bun.  It was 9pm, so hardly dining rush hour.  And it's bun, so most of the ingredients are cold!  We cut our losses and went to the fun Japanese BBQ place on Callowhill instead.  
Ok, we get that it was opening week. Mistakes get made. It's busy.  But employ staff who have basic customer service skills and treat local customers with some courtesy, otherwise they won't come back. 
We're going to give the delivery / takeout service a go this evening.  But if that fails, we won't be returning.  Customer service really matters in a big city like Philly. There are heaps of other great places to eat that have customer service down, so if you want to compete, let alone be a loved neighborhood eatery, fix this, and quick!

UPDATE on takeout - Zero customer service on the phone either. We're going to Pho Cali in Chinatown instead - ten mins wait for takeout bun and noodle soup (they know how to run a takeout business).  We might try iPho again in a few weeks, if reviews suggest they've got their act together.

Decided to enjoy a post church Brunch with the family and headed to Mimi's hoping they wouldn't be overly crowded. While there were a few folks ahead of us the wait wasn't long and the hostess even brought out a cup of coffee for me while we waited.

We were seated and greeted promptly be our server, I wish I could remember his name because he did a great job, checking on us regularly and was very friendly and engaging. 

The food was subpar, I didn't think the crepes and potatoes were very good and wished I would have ordered something else. My wife ordered the special griddle cakes and those were better and they also come with Eggs, toast and a meat side.

The kids meal choices were pretty good and overall everything was reasonably priced.

Our food took longer than expected but they brought out some fresh muffins to hold us over which was nice and the server checked on us several times to make sure we were ok.

Overall I wouldn't come here expecting much (it is a chain) but it does the job and I think if you stick to something simple you won't be greatly disappointed. I will say I remembered the food being a lot better last time I came a few years back and was a little disappointed by the quality this time. The Muffins are great and the service made up for it and I think you have to know what you are getting going to a chain like Mimi's

One tip, $5 Mimosas Sat and Sun until 2pm and you can pretty much get a buy one get one entree coupon every week if you sign up for their club.

Almost every time we visit family in NJ, we hit the Blue Monkey. It's such a fun place! The burgers and salads are awesome, and I really like their French onion soup. They have lots of unique craft beers to choose from as well! Can't wait to go back :)

My family has been going to C&G for several years now to have our cars serviced. We keep returning to C&G because they are honest, dependable and are masters of their trade.

They exercise a high attention to detail and it really reflects in their work quality. We rarely, if at all, find ourselves returning a second time to have the same issue looked at because it's done right the first time. When you bring your car in, they will not only diagnose the problem and give you a recommendation but they will also give you a walkthrough of the issue and educate you so that you are fully informed to make the best decision as a customer. 

A few months ago, my work office moved far away from the north east, so I considered using a local Bucks county mechanic for routine oil changes etc.. He was highly rated, but much more expensive, and when I asked him to troubleshoot a larger issue I brought my car back to C&G and they were able to give me the same solution at a much better price.

Steve, Kenny and Aaron truly go above and beyond for their customers and I could not recommend them more!
I have had the pizza, calzone and garlic knots, all are very yummy! The staff is friendly and I have not had any bad experiences. Highly recommend!

Hold the artichoke please. Ok, honestly I'm a complete artichoke lover, but this was out of control! The biggest pieces of artichoke you've ever seen! It was hard to taste ANYTHING else. And out of the entire experience, yes this is what sticks out in my mind the most. 

But let me start from the beginning. We walked in and I really liked how the place looks. There's a clear "bar" section as well as a clear "restaurant" section. I wanted to be a bit more cozy so we opted for a booth in the dining area. Now that we did, I wish we would have sat at a table in the bar section. If I remember right, they have lots of windows on that side. We sat in a 2 person booth and it ended up being way to small by the time our food was on the table. 

We started with the spicy spinach artichoke. It is basically a piece of bread with spinach and artichoke dip on top. The bread tasted like dough, not flavorful or good. And the artichokes were so huge and overpowering it was hard to enjoy any of it! I did like the tiny taste of "creamy spinach" I got. I probably would never order this again. 

I opted for a wedge salad and a pizza but the waitress said "the wedge salad is huge, are you sure you want that?" Well, now that you mention it, no! So instead I went with a Cesar salad. It was completely drenched in Cesar dressing. Yuck. 

I got the pesto chicken and artichoke pizza. Another mistake. The artichokes were once again huge and overpowering. The pesto was ok and the chunks of chicken were huge. Won't order it again. 

My husband got the patty melt and loved it. He specifically commented on the caramelized onions with the house sauce saying it was perfection. He also ordered the truffle fries and was so excited about them. He said they lacked flavor and I agreed. 

So if this was my experience, why would I be back? Well, because I think this place has potential. The bar is huge and I had a cosmo that was absolutely awesome! They have a huge selection of beer as well and after reading the reviews on yelp, it sounds like they have a great happy hour! I will give it another try and order something very different when I do.

Brenda and Sandy ROCK!!  I changed to this Sun Country location several years ago after the dry cleaner who was much closer to me became less and less customer oriented.  From day one, Brenda and Sandy were attentive, professional and detail oriented.  I am constantly amazed by the level of service they provide, inspecting the garments when they return from the plant and returning them for things I might not have ever noticed.

While I don't expect perfection, the willingness to resolve an issue and their attention to detail to make sure even the most basic laundry item I bring in is done right and to a level far exceeding my expectation has made me a customer for life.  Sun Country should be very proud of these two ladies and recognize that they are both exemplary employees, and the reason why I and probably others come here.

New place practically around the corner from my home.  The place is very clean with bright, cheerful decor.  The staff is friendly and courteous.  Started with the avgolemono soup and keftedes (Greek equivalent of meatballs).  Soup came with a basket of bread and keftedes came with pita slices.  Both breads were piping hot, as if they'd come directly from the oven to my table.  Main course was Aegean seafood pasta, basically spaghetti and Greek-style sauce with shrimp and Parmesan cheese.  All in all it was a pretty good meal.  Not the best Greek food I've had, but it definitely did not suck.  It was a bit pricey, total (including beverage) was $36.80 for just one person.

Go here to get parts etc. The Mechanics know their stuff so I learned to go DIRECTLY to them, and you get taken care of.  But for the most part this is another one of those Mid City businesses that caters to the "new" cool crowd and therefore if you don't know someone there or don't look like a hipster NOLA cycler type you may get ignored, that's what happened to me at first until I started schmoozing with the "cool" mechanics and talking shop to get myself in the "in" with these dudes....lmfao.   I give them 3 stars....would be more...but because of their ultra pretentious attitude. and every time they ask me ..."you must not be from here".....even though I have been living in the neighborhood years before they moved in and tell them that EVERY time.  I just now know the routine and get my parts and pick their brains so I don't have them fix it charge RIDICULOUS prices.  The mechanics are actually more approachable than the huber-chill, cycling studs doing the floor and cash register....so don't feel shy to go up the mechanics instead and ask questions or get something you need. They are more helpful.

Came into the shop with a deck that needed grip, trucks, and wheels. I'm probably not the demographic that usually frequents a skate shop, but Spencer and Naren (sp?) we're great and provided us with a great experience. If you're in SB and need anything skate related, skip the corporate stores and the mall and head to Lighthouse. The guys will hook you up and you'll leave happy!

All I have to say is....try it!!! If you like cookie dough, it's pretty much a guarantee you'll like this. You only need a little bit because it's extremely rich. But so freaking amazing. Wish there were more locations!! I live in Pittsburgh and as far as I know--there are none here! 

Tastes exactly like cookie dough. I had the basic chocolate chip, perfect!

Just had my first little cake from here and it was delicious! I had red velvet with chocolate chips and cream cheese icing. The texture of the cake is great, very moist and light. The icing was fantastic. 
Nothing Bundt Cakes delivered a sampler to my office for free, and I will definitely be visiting their store now!

I liked everything about my experience with Phil. I ordered the wood by text message on a Saturday and he was able to deliver on Thursday night. I bought the 6 bags and paid cash so I also got a bag of kindling. Phil and his guy came right on time and even though there was a lot of snow on the ground they put the wood on the back porch. I have had the wood for a couple of weeks now and it's high quality wood that burns very well. It might be a little cheaper to buy wood by the cord or half cord but I found this super convenient and it's definitely the best quality of wood I have ever gotten. I would highly recommend this service

Todd is a great bar tender! It was very busy when I came in with my fiancé but he was very patient and listened to all our bs in the middle of making all the drinks. You can definitely tell he's from Bourbon St! Very very friendly and made our experience memorable. I wish we lived closer! We highly recommend this place. Thank you Todd!
One of my favorite restaurants out there. Not only is it gorgeous indoors and out, it has great food and a very friendly staff. I have been there a couple of times and was never disappointed!

This place is outstanding!!! From customer service to exceptional food! I absolutely have been recommending this new spot in Santa Barbara to everyone I know!!! First impression was great! This is how a restaurant should be ran. Sensational! Love The Honor Bar!

I've been to 2 other Tampa locations but none of them are as delicious as this one. The chicken kabobs are my FAVORITES and the fries are the best! I'll also add that the owner is very nice! I ordered fried on the phone, when I picked up the order, it was rice (easy to misunderstand on the phone). He corrected the issue, and I left full and satisfied. Thank you!!!

Wow, what a let down. I found out this location was around the corner from work so, thought I'd stop. First,  good luck finding it. Awful location. Second, there are not many books and the ones I did see were over priced. Not a fan.
Friendly attendant who supplied all things for my dog's bath- shampoo, conditioner, ear cleaner, Furminator etc and no time restraint thus he left very clean. Definitely recommend.

I have been visiting Kolache factory for years but only recently began using their online ordering service.  It is so simple!  If you are looking for something other than your usual bland bagels for your office or for your customers, I highly recommend the Kolache Factory. They offer party trays and a wide array of flavors to choose from.  You can stick to breakfast inspired Kolaches, fruit Kolaches or even pizza stuffed Kolaches.  They even offer trays of dinner rolls that you can take home and bake yourself (perfect for the holidays). If you do decide to walk in and order in the store, the process is quick and simple!

What a really cool funky spot!! My husband said hands down best bacon he has ever had, it was smoky, crispy cooked perfectly. Food was fresh and hot. Our waitress was lively, she was singing to the songs. Overall great vibes and great food.

I have been going here for quite some time, as I live close by. My daughter took me to get my nails done for Mother's Day recently. I got a gel mani and pedi for $70 plus tip. It was horrible! My toes were left bubbly and bumpy, old polish was obviously used. My gel manicure was not much better. The work was sloppy and I was treated as an inconvenience. They were trying to save time by doing my medi/pedi at the same time, it was not relaxing at all. They were trying to hurry up and get it done while obviously talking poorly about me in their language. I believe one woman was the owner too. If you want sloppy, subpar, expensive work done, this is your place.

Southgate is one of the best malls in the city, I find. It's my second favourite mall in the entire city because it's got some great stores and selection. I don't think too many people come here though, because it's all the way on the south side, and for most of the local population that's far. But for those of us who do live on this side of town, it's great. And being in the south, it's one of the newer malls in Edmonton as well.

They have some unique stores that you can only find here, like the Science Shop and RW&Co. Other stores include Sears, The Bay, Gap, American Eagle, Stokes, and Lord's Shoes. You'll also find many services here, from medical and dental to banking and hair salons. They have major hair salons here like Hennessy and Eveline Charles. There's also a Safeway attached to the mall.

While they don't have much in terms of mall entertainment like West Ed does, they still offer a lot for shopping. There's a mix of high end brand stores with more affordable shops for those who don't want to spend too much. It's all about the shopping here at Southgate.

They're undergoing some huge renovations right now, since the city is planning on expanding the LRT and connecting it to Southgate. Needless to say, the roads outside the mall are currently a big mess, and they recently moved the bus terminal across the street, closer to the mall. It's a bit frustrating right now, but I'm sure it's going to be great when it's all done. And then everyone, not just south-siders, will be able to enjoy Southgate!

Wow this place is great. You can tell it is a stand alone with the owner and family doing the cooking    I have mostly had pizza and salad both of which were excellent.  I really love this place and I've eaten pizza all over the world.

Tonight I had some pesto that was so delicious it reminded me of my Nonni. I'm honestly shocked that I have never been here before the food was excellent! We started out with some wonderful iced mint tea and a Oh Honey Board. When it arrived to our table the aroma was overwhelming and almost made my mouth start watering. Fresh made to order bread with honey, goat cheese, and olive oil, superb. She had the calzone and one bite oh my gosh sooo good. I ordered the Pesto pizza and one bite brought me back to when I was a little kid and my Nonni use to make me fresh home made Pesto it almost brought a tear to my eye. Thank you for the special memory and the wonderful dinner!!

This place is simply amazing. Excellent Southern style food sir family-style. Be prepared to sit next to people that you don't now but I feel like that's what makes it a nice place to eat. Their fried chicken was to die for. The meatloaf was amazing. The green beans were super.  The service was excellent. The restaurant is inside of a historic mansion. So when you're done eating you can walk around and look inside the house. It's right by the airport so I we were done eating we set on a lawn chair and watch the planes land and take off and that was pretty fun. I highly recommend this place but come hungry.
Great food, all around great service. Robert T was amazing. The hype surrounding the charbroiled oysters is real. Try them!
Was looking for a little cafe that sold sweet barbque beef and hit the jackpot with Mano's. It is exactly how I like it and to top it off their onion rings are the bomb!

We went because the Taco Oriented Menu looked interesting. The restaurant fell short of expectations. This is a new restaurant with a high ceiling that amplifies noise quite effectively producing a noisy environment. This inconvenience is made worse by very sparse bench seating which gets uncomfortable. The dishes are served on metal trays adding to the Army Canteen ambiance. We ordered the Steak Nachos, a Breakfast Brisket and egg Taco and a Brisket Sandwich on a Brioche bun. With a beer and a Diet Coke the tab was $46.50! Not a good value. Our server was very pleasant and helpful but the food was OK, just OK. The Steak  Nachos would have been a better value with more steak which tasted good. The Brisket Sandwich was on the dry side The Egg and Brisket Taco was OK, Nothing inspired. Maybe Loud Pub style places appeal to you. If so, go.

Coffee was delicious!! I especially love their iced lattes it keeps you coming back for more! When I initially went there I was not happy with one of the servers and their attitude- Specifically the way they interjected themselves to something i didn't even ask them/belittled feeling- I waited a whole 25 minutes after they made a point to tell me exactly what i was ordering- I also noticed them roll their eyes to one of their customers - besides all that the coffee is amazing and all the other servers are really helpful and kind!

STAY FAR AWAY, TOTAL SCAM! THIS COMPANY NEEDS TO BE SHUT DOWN. First, check out their BBB rating, the owner's fraudulent history, the complaints via the Attorney General and Hillsborough Consumer Protection Services reviews- it's UGLY.  They didn't have the vehicle that I booked two months in advance and charged me the same rate for a lesser vehicle. Second, the check-out process took over an hour and a half. Third, they try to tell you that there are new tolls on the highways and that you'll be charged a much higher rate after the fact and get you to sign up on their service, this is a smaller scaled scam- do your research on your route(s). Fourth, upon returning the vehicle, Brian A was literally kicking the bumpers to inspect the car and even lifted up the hood- seriously?! He found a "crack" in the windshield, thus the ridiculous scam and fraud ensued. Brian A and Pony (a joke who calls himself a manager) saw us coming a mile away and tried to force me to sign papers saying I was in an accident and fraudulently charged my credit card $500 without my consent for the "deductible". There was no accident and they weren't even smart enough to file a claim with my insurance company that was on file.....Thus I disputed this with my credit card company and two weeks later Executive tried to charge my credit card in retaliation- again, not the smartest people working there. Luckily, the Attorney General of Florida is investigating them and the Consumer Protection Services office are great to work with to help in this situation. THIS COMPANY NEEDS TO BE SHUT DOWN

First time I walked in, I felt like I was hit in the face by the noxious odor of peroxide, but because of the low price, this was a school after all, I thought I could come back at a less crowded time. There were to receptionists and only one was handling a customer, the other just looked at me and said nothing. 

Second time, I was determined to try a cut and this time it wasn't crowded, the smell wasn't bad so I stayed, and the girls at the front desk were both friendly. The stylist was very polite but very disorganized, dropping things and having trouble with the chair, her table not ready with the tools she needed - but she was a student so I opted to ignore. All I wanted was a blunt cut and the length just above my shoulders, no bangs. She was going to start cutting without washing my hair so I asked, and she said, ok and she did a good job with the wash - but I'm not sure about the shampoo and conditioner because it kind of burnt my scalp or maybe the sink was not well rinsed after previous use - but I chose not to mention it.

The girl was very careful which I thought was a good sign and asked me several times if it was all right. I thought she should have cut off more but since my hair was wet I thought I'd play it safe and just go with it. After she was done, her instructor came to check the work, did a few extra snips and said it was good - and I believed her.

When I came home, dried and straightened my hair making it about the same length as when it was wet and being cut - I saw it was the most UNEVEN CUT of any place I've ever been to in my life - and I've had student cuts elsewhere too, but never like this. Blocks of hair in all different lengths, a whole group of hair that never got trimmed, what an embarrassing mess. I chose this place because it was a simple job and a supervisor would do a final check - but if the instructor couldn't get it right for a simple straight cut this is a total fail regardless of the price. 

And now that I think back, that sink where my hair was washed may not have been totally clean of chemicals when I had my hair washed hence the burning sensation . I do not recommend.
Great fried breading. Really enjoyed the juicy chicken tenders. Definitely eating here again the next time we're getting a family fried chicken meal.

What a great discovery!  The "In Living Basil" burrito sized spring roll is delicious and filling!  The fresh ingredients, Tamari mushrooms, tempura tofu and maple avocado dressing (on the side) is a perfect blend of flavors.  I was a bit hesitant of the maple avocado dressing because I thought it might be too sweet but it wasn't.  It has just the right hint of sweetness.  I will definitely be back again!

Amazing!! I love this place so much. I went on a Saturday night and they had live music. The patio is gorgeous with lights and a fountain with turtles! I loved the drinks and the food was tasty too. Their patio set up is the best part, in my opinion. Go if you are all about ambiance!

Great place I found today thanks to Yelp. Near home first, this is why I went there. But, most of all, great service at reasonable prices. With the technically challenged customer I am,  the person in charge was gracious, patient, explained what could be done clearly and simply and my job was finished rather quickly. The place is spacious, with some relaxing music. I will go again!
Not bad, not bad at all. I concede that the selection is fairly limited, but if you don't mind a good old-fashioned/sour cream, it's worth swinging through if you find yourself passing by.

Beautiful restaurant located in a great neighborhood! My husband and I showed up 5pm on a Friday without reservations, but were happy to find that the bar was wide open with plenty of seats for the taking and the option to order off the dinner menu. It was certainly busy by the time it was 6 p.m. so be sure to either make a reservation for a table well in advance, or get there early enough to snag bar seating. 

Food-wise, it's tough being a vegetarian looking for a fine dining experience in the south. But, 5th & Taylor at the very least provided a great atmosphere and enough options for us to piece together a full meal. We ordered the beet salad, asparagus, Brussel sprouts, mushrooms and the cauliflower steak entree which was served with greens and mashed potatoes. I was super excited when I saw this offered on the menu, but it was just OK (as cauliflower steak usually is, in my personal cooking experience). The mashed potatoes were tasty but a bit too runny  -- when the server put them down on the bar my husband literally thought it was a soup, hah. Between all of the sides we ordered (and those potatoes), it was too much butter/oil for me and you bet I needed to pop some TUMS before bed. 

That being said, I would still go back in a heartbeat for the atmosphere, that delicious strawberry basil sangria and those Brussel sprouts -- I loved their unique take on them (mustard instead of balsamic vinegar!). The beet salad and asparagus were also very good. Not to mention, the service was excellent. :)

Seriously in love with this place. I missed my train and had to wait 2 hours for the next one. The decor is absolutely perfect with a rustic chic vibe right on trend and very clean. Good amount of space with the inside and outside seating. Steady flow of people but not over crowded. Amazing playlist, great service by Ali, the food was good and came quick. I had the avocado toast with an egg and a caffé latte. If I lived here I would wake up early to come here everyday. I am going to look for something similar in LA. Stressful morning turned relaxing and enjoyable. Thanks Rebar!
Very friendly service. It wasnt express so dont get bent out of shape. I would visit again.

The live music initially lured us into Cerveza Jack's, but the potent drinks and ingenious food are what kept us there.

We had the guacamole and chips (also comes with salsa) and two tacos.  Our server recommended the cheeseburger taco.  It sounded strange, but we decided to go with it, and were glad we did.  The hot chicken taco was also a winner! To wash it all down, I had the candied jalapeño margarita.  Perfect amount of heat and paired well with the apps.

Check into yelp and the tacos ($5) are BOGO. 

Around the corner from Broadway, it was a nice change of pace.  Plenty of seating, great music and good eats.

The worst food ever. Starting from our first horrific appetizer my family and I worried about the rest to come. Dish after dish we went from bad to worse. They spent so much money in making such a beautiful place, all details in place but they don't have cooks that know what they are doing. Appetizers were either too salty ( nasty salty) or overpowered by sauce. The ramens and udons were seasoned either with too much salt or too much spice. Everything was spicy as if adding a spicy touch to everything is a must for flavor to occur. Everything we tried was one dimension. No complex flavors, nothing exciting in other words bland. I almost felt I was attending a cooking class with a bunch of amateurs in the kitchen and me being the guinea pig.  With a $100 tab at the end of the meal and a subliminal message saying gotcha!We left this restaurant to go to another so we could eat. Our server asked us when he saw that we barely touched our food but nothing was done for us and all the dishes were charged with no remorse.  If you want to blow your money for a tummy ache, this is the place. Good luck!

What a treat!! We ended up here because who doesn't want to go eat at a place called Vampire Penguin??!!!!?

Shaved ice desserts.

Ordered: s'mores & strawberry cheesecake 

Great!! Best part is the dessert is much lighter than icecream!!

i love this place, its great to find things that a regular grocery store might not have, also good for finding a quick snack and if its a nice enough day eat out side because they have a few tables on the side of the store. just found a great new seasoning that has some chile peppers from south africa. the person i spoke with seemed knowledgeable about the products i was wondering about. also not a bad beer and wine selection for a inexpensive price.

A lovely dining experience with great food, good wine in a very nice setting.  To start, the bread was crunchy on the outside, moist in the inside and flavorful especially with the flavored butter.  The salad with the house dressing was tangy and creamy at the same time. My Pollo Russo was very tasty as was my husbands Vitello Picatta.  The marinara side was very good.  All the food was very fresh with just the right amount of seasoning.  The server was very attentive but not pushy.  The evening was a very nice dining experience.
For the thrifty, they are in the Entertainment Book, buy 1 get 1 and also on Restaurant.com

Service could have been a lot better! We ordered a pizza and they brought out 3 mini pizzas on flatbread, never asking if that was ok. The bartender just say it down in front of us and said "oh I guess they ran out of pizza dough" and walked away. When we said something about it they took $2.50 off our check.

Updated 9/17/17:

Food has significantly improved. Pricing is still the same but quality has improved! Happy hour is $1 off full pours. Server is friendly and willing to give suggestions. 

*  *  *

My husband came here Friday night around 8 for dinner. It was pretty busy for a Friday night in June.  We were seated promptly. The beer selection  is solid and anyone can find a style they like. They have a variety of pour sizes, which is good for those who do not like to commit. Unfortunately, flights are not available. They do have take out beer as well. Unlike the previous beer hall that occupied his space, there is also cocktails and spirits available. 

Since it was busy, it took a while for the server to come to our table. We put beer and food orders in. Some of the food came out quicker than our beers came. The bar seemed to be stacked with bartenders but very few servers on the floor. No wonder why the service was slow. 

The food is from food trucks currently. The food was heavy and filling, but overall not satisfying. In addition, it was very expensive for what it was. A six inch brisket cheesesteak with no side was $10. The truffle fries were $6 and pretty much the best part of the meal. 

Overall, I would come here for happy hour because of the variety in beer selection. I will wait to come back for food when they are serving from their own kitchen.

Wanted to try out the new place in Channelside, walked in, bartender said sit wherever you like so we sat and waited and waited and waited. No one ever came up to us so we just ended up leaving. I doubt we were missing much from what we saw.

The only nice thing about the experience was we sat next to the windows which look out to the dog park, hard to be in a bad mood when you see a bunch of dogs running around. 

Happy hour was $2 domestics and $5 Tito before 7pm, not that we got to enjoy that...

I've watched a couple of movies here at UA Riverview Plaza for three reasons: (1) it only takes a short drive from old city; (2) it has plenty free parking under the bridge; and (3) it has more screens than most movie theaters in the city, which means more movies & times are offered. It does the job of a movie theater -- you can watch movies here.

However, this place has minimal maintenance: old facilities, squeaky chairs, dirty restrooms, and closed refreshment shop on the second floor. In this sense, you won't have the best movie theater experience here.

You talk about a restaurant that just reminds you of southern hospitality! Mother's is an old school / cafe diner serving up some mean southern / Creole soulful goodness. I got probably one of the best fried chickens ever, coated in perfect corn meal blend and juicy as can be. Sides of red beans and rice and turnip greens, both of which cooked with their ham is quite the perfect meal. Get a Bloody Mary to wash it all down. It will punch you in the face in the most delicious way; they don't mess around with that right there.

Ignore all the negative reviews you've read about this cafe! I went there this weekend for brunch with my family (17 people total!). We did have a 30min. wait but boy was it worth it! Not only did they accommodate our large party but the service was  perfect. Meanwhile, we must've ordered more than half the menu. The red velvet pancakes($10) lived up to all the hype! The creme brulee waffles($11) were to die for, the atlantic lox & eggs($12) was like a party in my mouth & the stone grounds grits($5) were THE BEST I've ever tasted! The only thing we all agreed wasn't very good was 'the kitchen sink($10). The biscuits were like bricks, so dry you could choke on them. Lastly, the coffee gave Starbucks a run for their money & the food portions were gargantuan! Not one of us were able to finish all of our food!!

This family owned restaurant has an awesome all you can eat menu! 

The service is great. The food is good and the beer is cold. The all you can eat menu is reasonable, even if you are a light eater, you will get your money's worth! I had about 3 rolls and an appetizer, which was more than my usual sushi order and still felt that the price was fair. It was about $30 (maybe a few dollars less). There aren't many places in Marana like this, so if your tired of tacos and/or fast food, give this place a try. 

Happy Eating!

I was also present at the Sharpizza incident last week.  Let me start by saying I am a fan of the quality of the pizza that this place puts out but running a business doesn't only require good product, good service is equally as important.  I know this and I don't even own a business myself.

Assuming that 99% of the food they make doesn't have foreign objects in them, it would seem that providing a refund to the customer of a product such as this wouldn't be a big ask.  Being in the customer service industry myself (again, not a business owner) this is a simple fix that might financially burden you momentarily but benefit you in the future.

This isn't only a Sharpie on a pizza pie, its a permanent mark on your reputation.

I was contacted by Buca di Beppo personally and we discussed the service issues I had written about. They were very apologetic and have offered to help in making this right. They did seem genuinely concerned with our feelings and really we appreciate it. My parents would enjoy a return visit.

This place is a great choice for a different dinner.
It is very entertaining to watch and interact with the chef, while he is in front of you preparing your meals.

I gave 5 stars not because this is a world class restaurant, but because they offer a good value for the money you pay.

It is a good time, a looooot of food, cool experience, so yeah, I am definitely going to return here.

We will start with a disclaimer... my review is based on everything I got to try from the menu at the most recent Yelp Elite Event held here.  So when it comes to things such as quality of service or value for your money I can't speak to those things. It was a night where the food was served buffet style rather than table service. I will say that the staff was more than friendly to me the whole night, and the value was tremendous because I ate for free, so there.  

And in the interest of fairness, I will acknowledge that you're probably thinking to yourself that since I was treated to a free night, it might cloud my review.  I will assure you right up front that I will be as honest about the fare here as I possibly can.  Truth is, not everything completely wowed me.  But I'll also grade taking into account that food quality is always different in an atmosphere where it is served from catering trays rather than presented fresh from the kitchen to your table.  

Now, I can be a very detailed reviewer when I want to be, and truth is that I kept a nice little list of everything I sampled on my iPhone notepad.  So I'll just go straight into the list and review each dish I tried one by one.  Because in the end, I attend these events only so I can provide you the most detailed reviews possible.  By the way... you're welcome!  

Pizza... right off the bat, I'll tell you about the star of the menu.  The pizza here really is fantastic.  We spoke briefly to the chef, Luca Sena, Jr, and he seemed to take great pride in his pizza, especially the dough.  It is wonderfully fresh, no question, and it makes the entire pizza better.  The Margherita pizza was quite good, the sausage was better, but tonight he put out a seafood white pizza that quite honestly was out of this world.  I didn't see it on the regular menu listed on the website, but if it is available on the night you visit, I highly recommend it.  My wife also raved about the Margherita and the sausage. It was definitely her favorite dish of the night as well.  

Lasagna Cupcakes... they sound completely wonderful, don't they?  The concept is a lasagna base serving as the "cake", with ricotta "icing".  Very creative.  Truth is, they taste more basic than the concept.  But, I don't consider this a bad thing.  I sampled the sundried tomato ricotta lasagna, and it was good enough that I went back to try the truffle ricotta lasagna.  I do suspect that they might be a little fresher directly out of the kitchen, but they were definitely tasty.  Maybe not quite on the level of getting lasagna in a legit Italian restaurant.  

Guacamole and malanga chips... I love fresh guacamole done right, and this place does it right.  Another winner.  The malanga chips are a lighter taste than your basic corn tortilla chips, and most definitely the perfect compliment to the guac that they serve.  Great combination by the chef!

Braised short rib... another dish that I suspect would be a little better served from the kitchen rather than a serving pan, however it was very tender with a nice rich gravy.  

Salmon... I'm not sure if they served it in the same manner that they serve it on the menu, but it was a very fresh piece with a sweet tangy sauce.  

Seafood and Fregula... quite a unique dish.  I did enjoy the mix of seafood in the dish.  I'd probably enjoy a full dish of this right out of the kitchen.  

Tater tots... I have seen previous reviews and I know that this is popular.  I'll come out and say that the ones I tried were good.  But I wasn't overly wowed by them.  It could be that again they weren't served as fresh as normal.  I'm betting that they're much better right out of the fryer.  

Crab cannoli... this was a surprise.  They mix crab in with the Marscapone, fill a cannoli shell, and dust it with powdered sugar.  At least that's how they served it tonight.  On the menu they serve it with tomato sauce.  I applaud the creativity.  I'm going to say that this didn't work for me.  The tastes felt like they didn't fit together.  Maybe it's a personal taste.  

Tiramisu... this was definitely as good as any Tiramisu I've had at Italian restaurants.  You won't be disappointed.  

Chocolate ganache... my wife loved it.  I simply liked it.  I thought the chocolate could be a bit richer.  But I certainly finished it off happily.  

No complaints about the cocktails.  The wife and I both highly enjoyed hot apple cider with spiced rum on the heated patio.  It was a perfect combination and a fantastic atmosphere.  A taste of the house sangria also went down very smoothly.  

I can see where many would think the menu isn't on the same level as the finer places in Center City.  This place does seem to have a heavier bar atmosphere than a restaurant feel.  But overall, I thought there were more than enough quality items on the menu, especially the pizza.  I can see this place being a perfect choice for a gourmet pizza and a craft beer.  And that's never a bad thing.

if your a serious shopper and money is not an issue then this is the mall for you.  I can't say anything negative about the Mall.  It seems to have every store that exists in the U.S.  it's just too big for. There are certain stores that I shop at, and I personally found it irriating that I had to  go in one building, and drive to parking lots over to search for another store I wanted to frequent.  They overall tried to localize the high end stores, Rolex, Luis Vuitton, etc, but  there are many low end and mid level stores, mixed in, and I have to muddle thru many stores where I couldnt afford a key chain from. For those who are rich, you will love it.

A honky tonk sort of place with decent food and a bunch of TVs. I've eaten here for lunch a bunch of times while in town on business and cannot recall having a bad experience. The sandwiches, the wings, and the salads are all pretty good. Nothing super spectacular, but certainly better than average bar food. The waitstaff is usually prompt, so you can get back to work in a reasonable amount of time.

Cute breakfast place replacing the beloved but run-down Pot Bellys. What a difference some paint and new flooring make!

The menu is basic diner food. Most of it is breakfast, but there is a limited lunch menu. While I look forward to trying breakfast, I was there for lunch.

I had the bacon, avocado and tomato sandwich. It was served on toasted rye. The flavors were good. The menu said there was bacon jam on it, but if there was, I didn't detect it. The sandwich came with french fries, and they were very crispy and well-seasoned.

Service was friendly and efficient. This is a good place for a quick bite.

It was good. The staff wasn't that friendly and seemed to be bothered when we asked for more water. It took quite some time before they brought out our check. Our waiter consistently check on the other customers and failed to check on us. He would not even make eye contact! I am willing to give them a second chance. If we get the same waiter I'll simply ask for a different one.

Having bottle service is KEY here.  The bar is always pretty packed.  I always have a good time here.  The roof has an awesome view and on a night with good weather it is perfect :) 

Pretty good drinks, awesome atmosphere and great view... I like!

Oh. My. Goodness!  Right next to the Holiday Inn Express you'll find this little gem.  The food was delicious and the watermelon agua fresca was a perfect complement to the food.  The owner is super attentive and sweet.  I ate there yesterday and I'm going back today!
This place should have 10 stars. The paesano was the best sandwich I ever had hands down. You just need to try it for yourself but bring cash.
Wow. Talk about a great experience. The music the food and finally the service make Nosh a must do when in Nawling.

I've been getting acrylic & liquid gel nails done here for over a year and have never been happier with my nails. This is like a goldilocks spot, and I've tried out a lot of other salons in Philly before sticking to this one. It has the right amount of quality, attention to detail, color selection (vast), reasonable pricing, good music, good snacks, wine and coffee, and good conversations with the ladies that work there. I've gotten my nails done by Hailey, Mai, Mei, Huilin, and Heather and it's always amazing. I've even moved away from walking distance from them but I continue making the trip because I know no other salon will check off all the boxes. Be sure to check them out!

A total disappointment. 

My significant other and I had seen plenty of raving reviews about Vyoone's - unsure if we hit it on the wrong night or what the case was. 

We had 6:30 reservations and snagged the last table in the courtyard, which had low, cushioned chairs - cushions were wet and being two gentlemen over 6 feet tall, the chairs were way too low to be comfortable. We had those swapped almost immediately. 

Someone came by to take a drink order, which took about 15 minutes for a Pimm's Cup and a Manhattan- drinks weren't bad but the service never got any better. The same host who sat us came by to tell us about the menu, and grab our order for an appetizer. 

Our cheeseboard came flying out of the kitchen- honestly in 5 minutes or less- but odd, right off the bat, being as I am from Wisconsin and know my way around a cheeseboard- why the two grilled baguettes for 7 pieces of cheese? The math just doesn't work out. 

After the cheeseboard, dinner went downhill- well I truthfully cannot even say that as our server/host (unsure who our server even was since we encountered two staff, however neither even introduced themselves) never returned to take our dinner order. After 45 minutes we asked for the check and decided to walk about without having dinner. 

When we brought this to the attention of the host- she did not seem concerned, and only asked if we would like our order taken by the time she came back to bring the bill. She noted they were short 4 servers (on a Friday night? That's an issue) - however this wasn't brought to our attention, again, until the bill was brought. Had she prefaced with that when she sat us on those wet courtyard chairs the first time- the tone of this review might be different. 

While I can't honestly review the food, the prices were steep ($50 for 2 drinks and cheeseboard with two pieces of bread). I wouldn't return, I wouldn't recommend based on the service, or lack their of, alone. Plus the ambiance is totally bizarre - for a place that has all of these raving reviews I wasn't expecting to walk into Christmas lights hanging from a hallway and purple lights lining the courtyard. 

Save your time and energy! The same street is lined with businesses that were booming for dinner.

Ordered carry out for family.  Salsa was tasteless.  Burrito entree was a glob of cheese on a tasteless chicken burrito.  Peeled back the cheese and tried to enjoy the burrito.  Sadly, it did not help.  Do yourself a favor and don't go here.

I cannot believe it's taken me 25+ years to try this place.  Wow I've been missing out!!  I've lived in the area for years and have driven by Persian Grill thousands of times and the parking lot was always full - now I know why - it's great.  My hubby and I finally tried it when we joined our close friends there who have been Persian Grill fans for years.  

The food was incredible!  Very tasty, interesting textures, healthy - nothing is fried, big portions.  For apps, we tried the hummus and one of the yogurt dips - Excellent.  The pita bread was like nothing I've ever had - so delicious.  I had a kabob combo - great.  The staff is very helpful if you have questions.  Also the service was friendly and efficient.  The prices are extremely reasonable.  We were all so stuffed from our apps and entrees we didn't have room for dessert!  Next time.  

I am not a vegetarian but for those of you who are - they have several vegetarian entrees.  

Reservations would be a good idea for the weekends.  

Don't wait to try this place!  It won't dissapoint.

Bright and inviting: lots of chicken choices with herb/lemon sauce or some strength of vinegar based hot sauce.  Garlic sauce helps offset a selection that was too hot.  They offer an Impossible Burger but I tried the falafel bites which were tasty. They were out of cassava fries which I had hoped to try.  Not much menu assist from the staff in making a selection as we had hoped, but ended up with a nice variety of small plates to try a variety of offerings.
Very nice new restaurant. Owners are super nice. The place is clean and the food is realllly good. Service is fast.

We came to buy chickens and some accessories. They were crazy short handed, but they still took the time to answer questions and pick out the right chickens for us. They could of definitely been a 5 star but there was a little too much effort to get help and some complaining from the staff about how short handed, they were, and who's job it was to do what. But all in all, they have a wide variety of products and healthy chickens, so good job! Shop local, enjoy life

Awesome brewery, a good variety of beer to choose from. There is a section of the building devoted to brewing and gardening supplies with everything you need to get started growing ingredients or starting a homebrew.

Easiest motorcycle purchase I've ever made! I decided to sell my Harley and purchase an Indian Scout. I couldn't strike a deal with my local Indian dealer. I decided to call St. Pete Powersports just to see if they had the model that I was looking for. Justin answered the phone willing to help me. Not only did they have the bike that I was looking for, we negotiated a deal over the phone and they delivered it to my home free of charge! Justin was very polite, knowledgeable and super to work with. I love my Indian Scout! Thanks Justin! I'm just sorry that I didn't get to meet you in person.
Fantastic homemade pastas. The service was friendly and quick. We will definitely return. Yummy sangria too!

Ava was in a rush to do my nails. She stuck a blade under my old fake acrylics and popped them off, was very painful. Nail tech seemed to be very stingy with the polish and kept insisting for me not to have other go get painted a different color and didn't want to put gems on my nails. Very rude kept talking about customers coming in. The nail tech next to us seemed amazing Leslie I believe her name was, she seemed to take her time.

Amazing service and an amazing menu.
The atmosphere is beautiful and open with tons of natural sunlight. This is the perfect place for brunch or meetings while in town.
I really love the Macha latte and the food is always incredible. 

Make sure to get fresh juice while here too!
The nectar is incredible. 
One of my favorite lunch spots in Indy.

The only negative is that its a little pricey for what you get. It is 4 star food, service and a 5 on cleanliness and decor. Everything was really fresh and good not quite five star on the food but really good.

Came here for the apple festival and it was mayhem!  Way too many people given the limited space.  What was initially charming in the morning became rapidly more harrowing.  Lines stretched around the block for a half-dozen or so food stands, and when I left, the congestion on the roads stretched for miles.  I had to drive about 7 miles just to get somewhere I could average greater than 10 mph.

A cute place, but I generally do not buy knick-knacks.  Interesting enough to experience once, but a bit far for me to go just to browse boutiques.  Closer places for that.

If you want to get back at a rude patron send them a cement mixer!!!

This place is phenomenal!
Wait staff rocks!!
Food and drinks are worth it!! Sunsets to die for!!!
Sand under your feet and great food beautiful views!!
So worth it

We have been using them for 5 years. Not once have we had an issue with the pool color, clarity. They show up weekly, brush the pool, put in the vacuum cleaner, check the chemicals and add chemicals as needed. 

There is no way I would trade the services they offer at the price they offer to do it myself.

I was really impressed with this Cafe.  It has so many different choices,  Greek, Mexican,  American,  good mimosas etc. Goodbyes to first Watch,  Benedicts, this place is number one now.  And so close to me. 
ServiceA+
food A+
Prices A+
Thank you for opening a good breakfast- lunch place in Bellair

We held our wedding reception at Cafe A La Cart and everything was perfect! Chana and Mark were responsive every step of the way and helped us build the perfect day. Couldn't have asked for the buffet lunch to run any smoother- the food was ready for guests exactly when we had requested and we got LOADS of compliments on the menu. They even allowed us to bring decor to make the space our own. Definitely would suggest their catering services for your next event!
Great addition to Edmonton's brunch options. The bacon and potatoes fried in duck fat were my favourites. Highly recommend.

New restaurant.  Very good food with varied selection.  We had the Dexter and Reuben sandwiches with alligator stack, which is like a crab cake, but with alligator.  Clean, attentive service. Excellent bar.  All reasonably priced.   I will definitely return.

This place should not be allowed to call itself a steakhouse. The decor is rustic, the staff is nice but the food is blander than a piece of paper. 
We both ordered the prime rib with baked potato and beans along with the clam chowder. 

Prime rib - I have never tasted a piece of meat with such little flavor. I wondered if it was just me but my mom said hers was too, she even asked how could you make something with such little flavor. Also, I ordered medium-rare and it was more like medium-well. Usually there is a flavor crust on prime rib, there was nothing. 

Baked potato - while wrapped in tin foil it was so damn hot it was like they cooked it in a microwave. Plus they put nacho cheese on it which completely ruined it. 

The beans - these were the only thing with actual flavor however it tasted awful, it was basically baked beans in taco seasoning. I had one bite. 

The clam chowder - I was fighting with myself on whether to get the clam chowder or French onion. Should've went with the French onion. The soup was so bland I had to douse it in salt and pepper, there were barely any clams and it was definitely mass produced and not house-made. 

I will never come back here. I was extremely disappointed.

From start the finish, I really liked this place. I ordered the Steak and Stout Hand Pie with a Ginger Beer. I absolutely loved both of them. The steak was so tender and wasn't fatty at all. This place really reminds me Pie Society in Georgia. I've been searching and searching for something equal in taste. And, I found it. Would I come back? Hell yes I would!

Portions were small relative to other Vietnamese restaurants, but it should be noted that a "super bowl" size is offered for ~$4 more.  Flavor was good and on par with many others.  A bit on the pricey side though for the portion size.  Not the kind of place you go to for ambience or decor  It was likely previously a Bob Evans and Saigon has done little to change that appearance.  Menu does offer many items that are not standard on other Vietnamese places which seems to make this a good place for the adventurous palette.

Did they switch the bread at JJ's or are they making it smaller? I ordered my sandwich and it looked like they used the Lil John bread. To pay $6 and receive something that looks like $3 was upsetting. I also ordered my extras to see that it would not even fit on the bread.

I feel obligated to let everyone know this is my first yelp review and I'm happy to say it is for my brunch at turning point. Brunch began with coffee. Not a cup of coffee, but a whole pot. Why would turning point does this you ask? For my convenience and I ducking love it. The food was great, obviously. As brunch finished up the waitress asked if I wanted a to-go cup. Again, who does this you ask? Turning point does. This wasn't a shit cup either, this cup was made for kings. I've attached a picture of the to-go cup for your convenience. Hopefully, you can see this cup because it's great. Have a great day. Go birds.

Everything was underdone and unappetizing.

I honestly feel like they're being expensive for no reason. The food didn't seem to be very high quality (it seemed like dollar store food), the service was sub-par, and the portions were nothing special. It was like $7 for a chili cheese dog, a chili cheese burger, and a drink. It was also like $4 for some disappointing bacon ranch fries.

I would have been much, much better off at Eegee's or Sonic. However, I can compliment them for the mini corn dog bites and the jalapeño poppers.

I actually have taken the time to add this business to yelp myself to tell people the honest truth about how crooked and much of a ripoff this place is..

Do not believe me go do a Google search for this place and see the 70 or so "raving" reviews written by the owner himself all pretty generic talking about how there staff is so friendly and packages are so great..C'mon who you fooling bro...You will find about 5 or 6 honest reviews by actual consumers who rate the place as AWFUL!!!!! and tell stories of being overcharged treated like crap and ripped off..

Once you sign up they will not let you cancel..if you want to they will charge you hundreds of dollars of fees i think mine was like 900 or so..the "salespeople" if you can call them that are pushy low paid/low IQ morons who try to force you into buying products you dont need or want and will harass you every time you go in..I work in real sales and would fire these people on the spot if I ever saw them hard sell like they do. Also they will lie through your teeth about the contracts you are signing as most people do not read them.

Also wink ease they charge you every time for like 2 bucks even if you have protective eye wear..

i NORMALLY JUST BLOW OFF A BAD EXPERIENCE WITH A COMPANY FOR WHAT IT IS..BUT AFTER DEALING WITH A PLACE AS FRAUDULENT AS THIS I WILL NOT REST UNTIL THIS PLACE IS SHUT DOWN AS THEY ARE A HUGE OVERPRICED SCAM..

IF YOU JOIN HERE YOU WILL BE OVERCHARGED-TREATED POORLY- AND HAVE YOUR CREDIT RUINED IF YOU TRY TO CANCEL.

Also take the time to read other stories of fraud in the filtered section on yelp

Come on a Sunday for the tri-tip. It's served separately from the restaurant but is delicious. They offer multiple sauces for the heap of meat.  

Fun place to hang out but just know it is a biker hangout.  Might be intimidating at first but if you stick around you'll realize how great the food is, the ambiance, and the music.  

Could be difficult to find parking as you just park on the side of the road. Also hard to find if you don't know where you're going since it's really tucked away.

I prefer to go to dinner at the restaurant. The meals are a little pricey but come with a TON of food. You're able to get a choice of chili or salad with your dish and then it comes with veggies and a potato dish (french fries or mashed potatoes I believe).  The inside of the restaurant is very cozy - fireplaces, deer heads, historic photos. It's great when you're driving up at night and the restaurant appears after a few minutes on the pitch black road. It's decorated in lights and just immediately sets the mood that makes you feel like you're farther from Santa Barbara than you really are.
Like getting pizza from a gas station or 7/11. Awful crust and nothing tastes fresh. Hit Cosmos or Little Italy which are both just blocks away if you want a decent pie.

Very positive experience. We replaced 5 cushions, had a short explanation on foam options, sat on sample cushions on stiffness choices, had cushions measured, foam was then cut to measure, reasonable cost for upgrade and I am sitting on one now. Go there with your cushions and come home with them completed short time later. Friendly, professional, satisfied. Tina and Charles

Came here for my birthday , and since the online reservation asked about "special occasions ", staff wished me happy birthday which was nice 
Started with fried oysters, quite good. Light breading, crisp with tender oyster inside. 
Next was the half filet and lobster tail. Steak was a perfect medium,  nice and rosy. Excellent sauce bearnaise. A half filet is about 4 ounces which is a good size to accompany the lobster. 
"Death by chocolate " cake was good but nothing special. 
Excellent service from Scott  (hat tip)

Wow, finally a restaurant where we were pleasantly surprised all around in Tampa. The chef is truly an artist when it comes to combining flavors and ingredients. There are dishes that you wouldn't ever think to put together-- chorizo and octopus, for example-- that are outstanding! The prices were reasonable and everything we ordered was fantastic. I would recommend for a date night or special occasion!

First visit today for lunch and to watch a noon football game. Had been here many times when it was 312 and looked forward to trying it as really like the space. I didn't realize it was brunch only until 2pm so the menu was limited. I ordered the bbq wings as an appetizer and a brunch burger with fries for my meal. Wings were decent- could have used a couple more minutes in the fryer and less sauce. They were drowning in sauce. Burger was a smash patty and bland. Fries were blah (under seasoned and not crispy). We sat in the bar at a table. The bar area was busy and we were very happy with our server as he was very attentive (unfortunately he didn't tell us his name and it wasn't on the check).

A blondish bartender from Dino's with some pretty dreads hanging down her back, helped piece the wood bartop. No barn was harmed. The mosiac of small wood pieces was salvaged from a east Nashville fence. I think the varnished woody bartop looks as sharp as one made from barn wood everyone else seems to use. In addition to the Dino's girl, Crying Wolf owners also recruited a No. 308 bartender who knows mixed drinks. Tomato Fest gals mixed with hipster boys at the long TCW bar and at the smoking area outside on the big deck. The long bar is overlooked by a fierce looking Lone Wolf above. The wolf seemed to have a bit of a smirk, but maybe that was just the liquor on my imagination? The Wolf burger rocks, and so does the Dirt (not  Burt) Reynolds bacon/pepper/ jalapeno sausage. Good lounge food to go with good company at the Crying Wolf. The beer is affordable from the $3 PBR to the $6 Murphys Stout. The mixed drinks priced well to. Phase 2 will later see the far wall opened for a bigger room with music and more fun. TCW is HIP.

I had my first meal at their village location. I'm an outside sales rep and go to a lot of restaurants and found out they opened about 5 min from my house and was looking forward to trying it out. I was really disappointed. First The waitress was extremely rushed and gave me the rundown and then wanted my order ASAP. My side (fried deviled eggs. Tasted good) came out a good bit before my burger so I had the choice to eat my side alone or let it get cold before my burger. The burger came out and was good as well. However scarcely had a finished my side the waitress had taken my side plate and asked me if I needed anything else.(I'd only been in the restaurant for like 10min at this point). Then about 5min later( I was partially through my burger she came by to take payment.) Her handhelds were acting up so she had to take 3 trips to get another and then told me if it didn't work this time I'd have to use a different card. After about 3 min of trying to get my card to go thru with a partially eaten burger on my plate she had me get up and go to the counter where the card reader finally worked. 

After about 16min in the restaurant I've paid $26 for a burger and side. Then I get my receipt and realize I've been charged 2.5% for using a credit card? 

Food was decent but unfortunately after this I won't be back.

Food was best of the best. However a few glitches - my wine did not come until the end of my meal, I ended up not drinking it and for a restaurant this pricey that hurt a little.  The table for 8 was in a corner I had to climb over chairs to get to my seat and basically could not get back out to use the restroom once everyone was seated. That would not have been appropriate for someone in a nice dress or an elderly person.  The fold out eaves of the table were slanted downward and so all my food on the plate dripped toward the bottom edge of the plate, my wine glass slid towards me, and the shot glass of brandy punch that came with my Mardi Foie appetizer almost tipped into my lap as the server put it down.  The restaurant was not full so it is unclear why they crammed a table of 8 people into a very tight corner and small table. Not what I would expect of a restaurant of this caliber. But the meal/food was memorable nevertheless, especially the Mardi Foie and souffle dessert.

Savona is one of the very best, period. The service is impeccable. The food has never failed to impress. The ambiance is great and the service is always top-notch. 

Savona has an amazing wine selection, and a great assortment of drinks. The bartenders are professional and can make anything your little heart desires. 

The food is delectable, and the menu will never fail to impress. Having eaten here numerous times, everything on the menu will impress and anything featured will blow your mind. If the featured items don't tickle-your-fancy the dover sole is always stellar. Fish is cooked perfectly, served table side, and the sauce is a decadent masterpiece. 

You are doing yourself a disservice by not eating at Savona.

Drove by to see if they were opened yet, and they had opened the day before!  An exciting time to try a new restaurant!  This is their 3rd location (University City and Glen Mills I believe were the others).  The concept is pretty cool and fresh - farm to table seasonal menu with most dishes under 500 calories.  It was hard for me to not make the comparisons to the Seasons 52 concept - SO many similarities, even down to the fire, wood, stone comfy decor.  But I am a fan of both places!

Vanilla lavendar mojito was unique and sweet, watermelon lemon martini was very smooth and not too sweet.

Waiter recommended basil pesto caprese flatbread was good.  Very flat (see pic) and light.  The other flatbreads looked compelling for a future visit - Jamaican jerk chicken and rock shrimp.

We tried the recommended Alaskan Halibut which we were told was a best of philly winner, and the cedar planked salmon.  Halibut was outstanding, on a bed of buckwheat soba noodles with a ginger teriyaki glaze.  Excellent taste and texture.  The salmon came out very well done (cedar was burned) and the waiter was quick to offer to take it back and make a new one.  The manager came over to apologize and offer dessert on the house - very nice touches and not unexpected that there will be some kinks to work out in the kitchen on Day 2.  Handled professionally and we enjoyed the meal and will definitely be back, especially since its so close to home.

Dessert were individual shot glass portions, nost under 250 calories.  The strawberries and cream was light and yummy, and the recommended chocolate covered banana cream pie was a standout.

So, kudos to the waitstaff for knowing the menu and being able to make recommendations, and for being prepared to calmy and efficiently deal with the inevitable growing pains.  The bar area is very nice, actually the decor of the whole place is very nice and inviting. I could definitely see meeting friends here for a drink at the bar and/or dinner or appetizers.  A great addition to English Village!

My husband and I were visiting New Orleans from Denver and made a reservation for Sunday night. I had been to New Orleans before and had been to several of John Besh's restaurants but had not tried Luke. 

We came a bit early and were told that it was a slow night and we could be seated anytime. We decided to sit up at the bar and have a few drinks (always sit at the bar when visiting places, you'll always get the best stories). The bartender Amelie was a delight and made us several perfectly balanced cocktails. Before we sat down to dinner, Amelie had shared several cocktail recipes with us that we promptly saved in our phones.  

When we were ready for dinner they sat us up near the kitchen, which you can look into while the chefs are working. We ordered the chicken liver pate as an app and I ordered the plum duck breast and my husband ordered the shrimp and grits. Both were outstanding. We didn't even ask our servers (Camille and Cheyenne) for dessert but could see that we were going all out on this meal and brought us two desserts. Two words. Salted caramel. Wow. 

The general manager, Robert so pleasant and accommodating. Top knotch food and service. 

It was really the staff, who went above and beyond to make sure we had a fab meal, that put this over the top for us. I'd go back again and again if I could keep eating like that and not be a huge fatty. The only thing that would've made this meal any better was it Chef Besh himself was in the house.  

By far, this was the "Besh" meal I've had in recent memory. You will not be disappointed.
G & E has the best prices on dog and cat food. I like shopping here because of their knowledgable and professional staff.  Great parking

Great food, great selection of booze. Ordered pulled pork, slaw, burnt ends, baked beans, mac and cheese, and peanut butter pie. Everything was great. Wish they had a couple more BBQ sauces and would love to see a creamy slaw and collards on their menu.

I love chocolate, so find it hard to pass by an artisan chocolate shop.  The chocolates here are very artistic, and there are plenty of choices in both dark and milk chocolate.  I had a dark chocolate balsamic vinegar caramel.  It was very good with a slightly exotic taste.  I also bought a Tahitian vanilla chocolate.  Also very good.  But my favorite by far was the blueberry-chocolate ganache in a dark chocolate shell.  It had the perfect crunch to the outside, and the filling was downright luxurious.  Before I leave Santa Barbara, I'm heading back to get a few more of those, plus a regular salted caramel in dark chocolate.  Well, "regular" except the chocolate shell is in the shape of a buddha.

I really don't understand the love for Birra. Our experience: 40 minute wait, caesar salad soaked in dressing and served with limp pita (made from the pizza dough, I guess), overly-salty pizzas, too-small table, gimmicky menu, and cheesy decor (+tvs!). There are a lot of great pizza places in this town, and this is not one of them.

After spending $500 for two nights you would think the service would be better!  First off there was very limited parking. Secondly, there was only ONE washer and dryer for us customers on the premisice. Thirdly, I see why the breakfast was free, it was terrible! The best part was our bath tub. The water was going down very slowly. We told the front desk and of course they did nothing. In addition our pillows had feathers coming out of them! Never again!!

I live in Baton Rouge where there are only two bubble tea shops that are somewhat decent. One day, when I went to pick my mom up from the airport in New Orleans, I decided to search for a place that sold bubble tea. I had about an hour until my moms plane landed, so I decided to go somewhere that wasn't too far from the airport. King Fu Tea it was! When I first walked in, I noticed that the music was blaring, which seemed to be the reason that people were shouting. This place is EXTREMELY loud! The decor is gorgeous though. I waited in line for about 10 minutes (it was crowded, on a Sunday) and when I got to the register I asked the employee could I order a taro and pineapple smoothie, mixed. She told me that they don't mix flavors. WHAT?! I have never been to a smoothie establishment where they couldn't mix flavors. So, I just decided to order a pineapple smoothie. After waiting for about another 10 minutes, I received my smoothie. The first thing I noticed was the horrific flavor of the "pineapple". It's like they used some artificial pineapple flavor and threw hard little pieces of pineapple in the smoothie. It tasted more like pineapple cough syrup. Also, the boba tasted like it was soaked in some kind of weird, disgusting artificial syrup. This was the WORST smoothie I've ever had. I wish Honey Deux hadn't shut down; their smoothies were DELICIOUS. They could also mix multiple flavors. I'll stick to the halfway decent shops in Baton Rouge. Kung Fu Tea SUCKS!!!

I did something at Vero Amore that I really don't do: I ate more because it tasted good. Seriously now - I almost always stop eating when I feel full, but at Vero Amore, it was so delicious, I sort of pushed the envelope. 

Two co-workers and I started with the Prosciutto Caprese Salad, which featured their homemade mozzarella, prosciutto, tomato, greens and basil olive oil dressing. Can I just say how much I love homemade mozzarella cheese?

We then had two pizzas: Pizza Checca, which has chopped tomato, basil, mozzarella, olive oil and garlic. While I liked the Pizza Checca, I really am a "sauce" person, so it wasn't my favorite. The other pizza we had was the Pizza Lussuria. I would like another slice (or two) right now. Really. Tomato sauce, Genoa salami, mozzarella, garlic, and crushed red peppers. It was delicious with a hint of spice. 

We also got the Ravioli Aumentare, an assortment of ricotta herb raviolis and crab raviolis with a creamy marinara sauce. 

We also enjoyed a lovely bottle of wine that our server recommended.

Overall, a great experience!

I'm a big fan of Dinics!   Everybody has their own go to roast pork joint in Philly, and this one is mine.  I always go for the roast pork with provolone and rabe.  The pork is always moist well seasoned while the juices run into the roll and make it juicy (not soggy) and delicious.

The contrast of the shrap prov with the bitterness of the rabe can't be beat.  The only thing you gotta beat is the long lunch line- so go at an off-peak dining hour.

Excellent place to celebrate a birthday! Wait staff was super nice, restaurant was clean outside and in, and the selection of delectable treats was astounding. My red velvet cake was very moist and tasty, plus enough for a second serving layer on. Definitely a must try for visitors!

Yessss!  I had a red chile chimi enchilada style and it was so good.  The enchilada sauce is on point.  The beans and rice are delicious.  So much flavor in the rice and the right level of moisture. My girlfriend had a michelada and said it was one of the best. We also had a plain cheese crisp and gobbled it up with the house salsa in minutes. We ordered a dozen tamals to go (only available after 11:30am), lest we come home empty handed and face the wrath of our family whose love of Perfecto goes back when he used to slang tamales in the parking lot of the Circle K and Safeway by the Rez. His tamales still taste the same and we still LOVE them.
The service was excellent! The woman who helped us checked on us often and made sure we were satisfied and comfortable.  
I'm so proud of Perfecto and his family for the come up.  Can't wait to go back and try more!
The pulled pork was wonderfully moist and the baked beans were perfection! I haven't had fried okra since I was a kid, and I gobbled it up here. The service was stellar too!

I can finally review this place since I have about 3 weeks before this summer internship is over.  I've been here for seven weeks and I can say that I love Nashville! Well... TN in general! There is soo much to do here its crazy!

The staff and employees at Vandy are the best! And people outside academia are also amazing here! Nashville is generally full of great, nice people who are willing to go above and beyond for anyone.

While I've been here I have tasted a lot of nashville's best and finest restaurants, explored belcourt theater (my favorite and a five minute walk from the dorm), went kayaking, hiking, modeled, danced at Nashville Ballet co. School (my favorite and a fifteen to twenty min walk from dorms), rode in the bed of a truck on the freeway ;P, went on the hilarious trash tour, etc. To list a few of the things I've gotten to do!

I couldn't be happier with my experience living at vandy/nash and meeting amazing people. Three weeks left and I am sad to leave lifeat vandy... obviously, not too crazy about what I came here to do, but its a learning experience.

The school is beautifully gorgeous in all its wonder. Its large and small all at once. Its a very prestigious school where everyone looks like models! :D

My absolute favorite salad spot. I've literally driven from Philadelphia to Deptford just to pick up a salad from here.  Everything is always fresh, the customer service is great, and the taste is phenomenal. HIGHLY recommended.

Five adults were seated upstairs tonight. It was a disappointing experience. The noise from children at other tables was so loud that even the server had to yell to be heard at our table. The noise was so loud we could not carry on a normal conversation. 

I had two guests from Germany who were in Indianapolis for the first time. They enjoyed the food, but not the atmosphere upstairs. 

Bub's needs to improve the acoustics of that space before I will ever agree to be seated upstairs again.

Bub's you let me down. You disappointed me tonight.

This location has TERIBBLE customer service. I had to ask an employee if I could place my order because I had been in the store for 5 minutes and still hadn't been greeted. After waiting for 10 mins, they got my order incorrect and had to wait an additional 5 minutes for another smoothie. They are standing around on their phones and drinking their own beverages. Needs better management. I did however enjoy my smoothie and wrap.

They make their own pasta!  And it is amazing.  I've tried maybe half the items on the menu over the past 2 years, and there isn't one I didn't like.  My personal favorite being the mushroom ravioli (alas, my wife hates mushrooms so I don't often order it since almost everything on the menu can easily be shared by two people- which makes the prices waaay-reasonable)

The staff was very nice and attentive while still being laid back.  I like the feel of these kinds of places much more compared to anything on The Hill and heaven forbid- Olive Garden-y places.

My parents just moved here and I visited over the holidays. I love this gym. It's one of the gyms you walk into and can tell that the owner or manager have spent time working out. All the machines are really clean and well maintained. Additionally, the placement of the machines makes complete sense. It was a pleasure working out here.

We've used them many times over the years and they're always on time and very pleasant.  
Brought me boxes when I needed and really great at packing! The owners are wonderful !

The great thing is that the food is good. Lots of vegetarian choices and a varied menu, Go for breakfast and lunch, Sorry to say that the waithelp is more interested in joking with each other than being efficient and making certain that your meal is pleasant. Slow service. Meals take a long while. They don't refill coffee like they should. Lots of used plates and cups are dumped into plastic containers really loudly. Staff banter takes precedence over service and customers. So, I'd definitely be happy if employees were managed differently. Won't be back for awhile.

My boyfriend and I were on a road trip and found this place on Yelp. I am so glad we came in. It's pretty much the most perfect bar--not too busy but far from empty; dark; solid variety of drinks; nice bartenders; hilarious bathrooms; board games and all sorts of arcade games.
