I've been a client for a year now & keep coming back because the staff is extremely friendly, very professional, and they go out of their way to make sure you are extremely satisfied. I've never had a nail break & I can go 3-4 weeks without any lifting, cracking or discoloration. It's because Tony uses the highest grade products and it shows. I always get compliments on my nails because of the unique & tasteful designs by Tony.
Pedicures are also very well done & last with no chipping or color fading. I've been going to Joli who is very sweet and attentive, but Ann & Linda are great as well. I've even brought my husband in for pedicures and he has very difficult nails and feet. Don't be afraid to go to Nail Art because of these older reviews, this a very comfortable, professionally run business with a caring staff.

Extremely good food, wonderful portions and great prices. The place was very clean and had an expansive menu. We had two empanadas, a lachata, a chicken milanessa which came with mofungo and salad and my dining partner had a beef criollo dish with red beans and rice. We took half of our food to go because the portions were huge. We then took two guava and cheese pastries to go and will dive in to those tomorrow. 

Would definitely recommend for a very good Columbian restaurant.

I thought this place was really cute.  The atmosphere was inviting and our server was quite amazing...  very knowledgeable.  She actually looked like Mays from Lucifer...  anyway....the food was different and interesting, in a good way. We tried to go back last week but they were closed ...  it was a Sunday.  I don't remember them being very expensive and the drinks were tasty...  not weak.
Good place for a casual date.  Great location.  Trendy!

Had the platter! Everything was AMAZING!!! Smoked chicken is hard to perfect, but this was probably the best I've ever had!! Both times I ordered it! Very tasty & not dried out!! Someone has perfected the recipe!!

The music is great and this would probably be a great place to have a cocktail and listen to the band. There's a big screen that was playing the football game, as well. For dinner, the service was just incredibly slow. I ordered a second drink that never came, no one checked in during our meal, and the waitress took a half hour to process our check.

I went 2 this medical facility two months ago and I received follow up care for an injured finger condition termed mallet finger which seemed2 go well at first but when I called to rescheduled follow up appt to actually move it up they told my physician was on vacation and that I could use their trauma unit for my follow up so I assumed I would c a specialized physician instead a PA seen me which I was disappointed with because I was not absolutely satisfied really never assessed my finger or explain next recommended course of action she was most likely filling in for regular physicians who were on vacation I'msorry when I pay $100 each visit I should c a physician I work as a barber so proper care of my hands r important and vital I just don't feel I got any response when I called back in the same week to b seen again I was told I would b charged an additional $100. I personally don't feel that is a good way of doing business I would rather give that $100 to the SPCA because dogs need good treatment just sounding off I would like to know that I'm not the only person who experienced such service

I really love the food.  Just remember you five types of coffee to choose from on the self service drip coffee bar or you can order espresso drinks from your table.  The menu is certainly unique, full of options, even for the pickiest of palates.  Enjoy!

Super cool concept that just hit Tampa. Being from Atlanta I have seen these before. If you haven't checked it out it is a must!

While traveling for work we grabbed lunch here as a group of 12. We all scattered as there are many restaurants to choose from.

ALL the restaurants looked appetizing. They range from BBQ to Ramen with all things great in between! I opted for a salad at Inside the Box which was amazing (review to come on their Yelp page).

They have large tables which was great for our tribe. The interior is industrial chic. Super clean! They also have seating outside. They even have a super cool looking hand washing station for all of us germaphobes :-)

They were doing construction inn front of the building which didn't interfere with parking at all. The lot is HUGE.

I will be back to this joint when I return!

I was able to schedule an appointment easily online, and I was welcomed as I came in and they were able to start the appointment promptly. Sam gave me  an excellent cut -- I've got short, wavy hair... not so easy! I appreciated that everyone was wearing a mask, with as much social distancing as possible, and very clean. I can definitely recommend Hair Cuttery and Sam in particular!
Atmosphere is really nice. Unfortunately the food was not good. They change the menu a few times so maybe we got a bad week. Service wasn't so great either.

This place is as authentic as any food you can find anyplace on earth. It's very Italian and very New Orleans, even though its 20 miles away in a godforsaken swamp (okay, its on the edge of suburban Avondale). Their Oysters Mosca -- oysters baked in a pan with olive oil, garlic and other good stuff -- are one of the true New Orleans classics. I don't like the chicken la grande that others go crazy over, but thats okay because i am an oysters fanatic. It's worth the trip, absolutely and without a doubt. Its pricey, but you don't need 4 entrees for 4 people. Three will do.

I had not heard about this local establishment until I discovered it on Yelp doing a search near where my little sister from Big Brothers Big Sisters lives as I was picking her up and taking her out for brunch yesterday. I had decided to check the place out based on the good reviews, and it did not disappoint. There was a significant wait, as was expected, but that's pretty much the norm for any quality brunch spot in town. And I want to make sure to mention now before I go on below about my experience regarding the owners and customer service. The owners take pride in their food and customer service and it showed.

My little sister (a senior in high school) and I arrived about 10:30 on a Sunday morning. There is a very tight parking lot behind the house, and I was lucky a spot was hidden in there because I had 7 month old son with me and I didn't have to carry him far or pull out the stroller. The place was packed and we were quoted an hour wait. It was beautiful outside and they have a large deck with wrap around seating and other chairs so most people were able to sit and wait. It was a beautiful and sunny 60+ degree day in February, so we didn't mind hanging out and enjoying the sun.

We were seated after about a 45 minute wait. Since I had reviewed their website and menu prior to coming, I knew that it was their owner, Jennifer, who took our drink order, then our food order. The food appeared to be a little slow to come out, as the patrons next to us who ordered right before us got their food after about 20 minutes or so after placing their order. This was not an issue as I know they were busy and make your food to order. So then I was expecting our food shortly after. But as time kept ticking away, I noticed table after table (about 4) get their food with no sign of ours. And since I was sitting by the entrance, these were tables that were being seated long after we placed our order getting their food. Since this was at least another 15-20 minutes later, I got up and asked the host if someone could just check on our order. I was not complaining, it was just at this point thinking our order got lost or ended up with someone else. Plus, I've been entertaining a 7 month old for a while now! So after about a minute, Jennifer came over to our table and seemed shocked that we had not received our food, and told us the entire meal was on them. I tried to explain that wasn't necessary that I just wanted to eat before my son decided he was too bored or hungry, but she ran back to the kitchen before I could. Our food came out within a few minutes and she apologized again.

Now, onto the food. I got the bananas fosters pancakes. I love anything bananas fosters, and these were delicious. Three fluffy pancakes were covered in sauteed bananas, walnuts, and that yummy warm buttery brown sugar rum sauce (and whipped cream). They were served with a side of meat of your choice and two eggs cooked to choice. They only offer turkey meat products, no pork. I got the turkey sausage since they make it in house, and it was very good. I got my eggs over medium, and they were slightly overcooked to about medium well with some of the yolk being hard, but that was not an issue. My little sister ordered just a plate of eggs, meat, and toast, but they allowed her to substitute a fruit cup for the eggs as she does not like eggs. Overall the food was delicious with multiple menu items I'd love to come back and try, from omelets to eggs benedict to other specialty pancakes and French toast options.  

They also have delicious fruit tea and a variety of drink options. I didn't know when I ordered but they don't offer free refills on their fruit tea, but Jennifer gladly refilled me with regular tea instead.

Luckily for me I happened to have cash this day to leave a nice tip for them since they did comp the entire meal for us. They obviously care about their guests and the quality of food, and I will definitely return with my husband or bring my parents when they come into town, especially since they don't eat pork and it's sometimes difficulty to find breakfast/brunch places that offer turkey options.
Very good food. Attractive interior. Friendly, attentive service. Most lunch entrees about  $9. Dinners  $12.  This is a welcome addition to Florissant.

This is a little place and seemed to be filled with locals. I felt super weird and out of place when I walked in but whatever. The server at the window has ZERO personality. She could have cared less than zero that I was there paying my hard earned money. She walked away mid order without a word. I don't know if southern hospitality is really s thing? But here, absolutely not. Now the food. That was delicious! The chicken was moist and crispy. The greens were good but a bit salty. But the Mac n cheese was wonderful. Go somewhere else. They are Non welcoming!!!!

As a 'tabletop junkie', I have been shopping Pink Daisy for 20+ years for wedding gifts and for myself. 

Linda is extremely knowledgeable and helpful. She has a wide selection and can order just about anything. She provided the highest level of service. 

She also carries a well-edited selection of baby gifts.

Truly a delectable experience. Service was impeccable and the food was divine. Don't miss the lamb shoulder- brined for 3 days it's heavenly.
Highly recommend this Israeli restaurant. Just be sure to make reservations far enough in advance!

This place is just awesome! So many games to choose from. The game masters (who walk around to answer your questions) really know how to set things up and explain things in an easy way, particularly if it's your first experience with a new game. Will definitely be back!
This is the nicest, most courteous & professional staff. And the massage chair in the waiting room is a nice touch!

I think that the perfect way to describe Sabrina's is as an upscale diner. It is the perfect little brunch spot in University City (they have another location in Center City, but I've never been there). My boyfriend lives really close so we stop here pretty often to grab a bite to eat. The food has always been fantastic and we love that they have new specials so often and how personalized the chef makes them!

Some rules:

1. If you like french toast, you have to try the Stuffed Challah French Toast. It is to die for and I don't say that lightly. It is just that stinking good. The portion is HUGE (it's really enough for two people) and I always wind up bringing some of it home. I like ordering it with a side of sausage and turning it into 2-3 meals. The stuffing is sweet with just a hint of sour to make it jive really well with the vanilla bean sauce. (Can you tell I'm a fan?!)

2. Don't be afraid to try the specials! My boyfriend almost always orders something off of the special menu and its easy to do - they change them frequently enough that you truly do have a limited amount of time to try them.

3. If you want a more relaxed experience, avoid peak meal times. The place is hoppin' and if you go around a normal meal time you may find yourself waiting quite a while, or crowded into a small table because that is all that they have available. We like to go for more of a brunch time and there is usually much less of a crowd. We rarely go on the weekends because it is just packed.

Overall - LOVE Sabrina's. Only place I have ever found that compares is Miss Shirley's in Baltimore, MD.

Absolutely dread electronics stores, but alas have a geek child who loves them. Two days before Christmas (I know, I know) I stopped in to buy the boy a capture card (nope, I'm clueless) but a lovely geek girl showed me several, asked which system he had (PSwhat?) and then what games he played and on what size system to help me figure it out.
Unbelievable got the last one. When you're shopping out of state and without tech support these folks are lifesavers.

Came here under recommendation from a friendly bartender over at Tomlinson's to try out their seasonal brown ale and got much more than I bargained for (the brown ale was stupid delicious btw).

1 thing to remember about this place: sit at the bar and hope you're lucky enough to have Cara as your bartender. Seriously, best server/waitress/bartender, ever. Friendly as can be, offered to let me sample some of their beer offerings (including letting me sample something that was just tapped), courteous, attentive and overall some of the best service I'd ever experienced at a bar, or anywhere for that matter. From her interaction w/other patrons, she's clearly a favorite around the place.

Food wise I ordered the appetizer fish tacos and the guacamole. Both were extremely tasty, and very cheap considering it was already "late night" when I ordered. Honestly though, some of the best grilled fish tacos I've ever had and totally unexpected.

Terrible customer service and a Nazi dressing room lady who thinks she owns the store. Dresses not of very good quality. Very rude older lady dressing room attendant. We left after being insulted by her a few times. I'm not spending my money and  being insulted at the same time. I work to hard...

This is an update. The manager of this store should def NOT have anything to do with customers, ppl or the public. What a BAD attitude! Walked away from the register when I stood right in front of her to pay for a purchase! I was fuming! And I still am! How do these ppl stay in business! We will not be back! The manager of the bridal department ( the only proper customer service we received, very nice) ended up ringing me up after I had to find her and ask her to ring up the purchase. If my daughter would not have already picked out this dress, we would have been OUT! What a horrible experience! Go elsewhere!! Can I give negative stars??

A big fan of this place but I'm noticing a ton of inconsistency and decline in service. Shouldn't the message therapists all have basic skills down and certain amount of experience? The range of professionalism is lacking. Kyria is the only therapist I can recommend as being incredibly thorough and gifted. Seriously, she needs to train everyone. The last one I had (Courtney) was super fast, cold and sloppy. No touch. And ended 10 minutes early. Once I had a Greg I think and he was horrendous. So bad. Like out of a comedy bad. I just don't understand how some therapists are super amateur and some are amazing. The bad ones I notice can never fit in your whole body in an hour...?! They just skip parts. This is all unacceptable. Please raise your standards. Require some solid experience. And do some oversight. Some people just aren't good and shouldn't be hired at this level place.

Sooo...not much to look at from the outside, S.O. wondered aloud, "whatcha wanna go in here for?" After half a Muffeletta cut in half, he's  thinking like I can duplicate these at home. Sorry, Charlie, Muffelettas are for Central Grocery to do. Fabulous.

This is a favorite steakhouse of mine, but I must say sadly this time the mark was truly missed! The crab cake is now full of filler and not seasoned, plates were hot, food cold and my ribeye was extremely tough. I was shocked and appalled by what I experienced eating and the fact that I'm typing this. It will definitely be a while b4 I dot the door again, I never usually have any issues here at all....

Totally nonresponsive! 1st problem I couldn't get anyone to return my call to tell me they received my MRI so I went to my appointment anyway and they found it after a long look. Paid  the $70 copays. Then met with Dr Bono which went fine, he recommended a treatment. Then met with Jonathan Schweitzer and he explained the process and that Carmen Pagan, the insurance coordinator, would call. She did 3 days later and left a message. I returned her call later that day and again 2 days later, no response. Called Johnathan and left him a message too. No response. Finally went to the office today and to my surprise they had not locked their doors. I picked up my MRI and start my search for relief elsewhere. The Doctors are probably good but management is incompetent!
Great margaritas and great fajitas!  The shrimp was particularly tasty, along with the queso.  A definite must try when craving good Tex-Mex!

Went with some folks from the office.  We were all in from out of town.  The wait was a hour but the 4 of us found a place at the bar.  Service was good and our bartender was good but food was just okay I had a pesto pasta dish with shrimp and crab meat.  There was very little crab and the pasta, especially for being pesto, really lacked flavor. I could barely taste any basil.  When I asked the others they felt similar.  It was okay but definitely not as good as we expected.

If I could give this place more than 5 stars I would! I came here for dinner yesterday  I started with the complimentary Blue Cheese Souffle followed by the Spanish Octopus, which was recommended by our server. For my entree I got the veal cheeks which was one of the night's special and finished my meal with the chocolate torte for dessert. Every dish was outstanding and the service was excellent! 10/10 would recommend.

Best local craft beers are here at the Schlafly Tap Room.  I've been going here for more than a decade now, and have fond memories of using the cute front entryway when it was in use.  Silly, sad, I know, but don't care.

Cask options are often available, as well as seasonals throughout the year - always something new and fresh to try, or just go with one of their regular winners.  For me it's the pale ale or oatmeal stout.

Pub fare is somewhat traditional with a skew towards some European (German) options.  Some of it is pricey but overall not too bad.  Pool table areas can get rowdy during prime hours.

I really like this Petsmart - although it is definitely on the more expensive side.  They have a great selection of items and the shelves are always stocked well.  I take my dogs to this location for their grooming and they've always done an amazing job with them.  The few concerns about the store is it's really not laid out very well for the amount of foot traffic they receive and there never seems to be enough help at the cash registers.  Even with those issues though I'll definitely be back.

APRIL 12, 13, 14 2012  SMOKE DADDY'S OPEN, MIKE HERE, ONE TIME EVENT!!!
COME ONE COME ALL!!! 
Mike is visiting and will be open for BBQ business, also sides, nothing else to speak of, Thursday, Friday and Saturday 5 to 7:30 basically. THIS IS HUGE.  SAME PLACE! EAGLE'S PARKING LOT.

I brought my parents here in October. It was my third visit (the first time was in Jan 2001 with my dad, actually). It was very disappointing experience.  It's pretty loud first of all but that is to be expected. It's also very popular so we waited for a while for a table. We were seated at a small table in the back (good because it wasn't as loud in there). When a larger table opened up across the way, we asked if we could move and they were very nice about moving us. The issues we had were with the food. I ordered the seitan cheese steak. I specifically had asked if it had dairy or eggs in it. The waitress said no. When I took a bite, the bread tasted like it had butter on it. So I had to scrape off half the bread.  My father ordered the veggie burger. He didn't like the taste and it fell apart. My mom got the duck and it wasn't prepared properly, either. So, overall, it was a rather disappointing experience at Monk's. The only good thing was the beer, unfortunately.  I don't think I'll be back.

Yet another disappointment today at California Tortilla in Sicklerville. I placed a phone order and confirmed with the manager I could pick up my order at the end of the counter near the door. I did not have to stand in line to get my call in order per the discussion I had with the owner. When I came to pick up my food there was only one employee filling orders and the manager was manning the register up front. So I had to stand in line to get my order I called in yet again! Is the problem here staffing, training? I am not sure.  What's the point of calling in an order and then I have to wait in a line to get it instead of a dedicated pick up like location like other businesses.  I don't blame the manager for this situation. She was professional friendly and polite. It just seems there is some kind of systemic problem at this location. The food is always good. It just seems like the service is regularly lacking when I go there. I use to be a regular at but I have been going less and less because of these issues. At this point I am not sure if I will go back to this location. Although I have only written two reviews on this location I have encounter multiple customer service disappointments. Not sure what they need to do here to correct this. I am just gonna go to Plaza Azteca from now on. They seems to never have this issue when I order out.

Great, cheap food! Bar scene, but still kid-friendly with plenty of arcade games (25-50 cents each). Decor is fun, but not too crazy. Not too great for groups of more than 6. I had the turkey avocado burger, definitely worth the try!
The kitchen is doing it spot on here as it would rival any place in East Nashville or the Gulch. A hidden gem!

I needed to fix my nails quickly and came in without an appointment. Here is a quick summary of my visit:
1) I was told to wait for 5 minutes, which ended up being about 20 minutes
2) their sign outside says free drinks (mimosas, champagne etc)- I wasn't even offered a glass of water
3) I asked for an acrylic refill, when they were half way through it turned out they didn't have paper forms and I had to use tips (which is last century and I haven't had it done for years)
4) the manicure master didn't speak any English, so I constantly had to look for someone to help me translate 
5) the quality of the gel polish is really bad
6) I didn't see any sterilization equipment, which is really really bad, you can easily contract some sort of a disease 

Overall I had a terrible experience, will definitely not come back and would not recommend this place to anyone.

Stayed with my wife and five year old son last weekend.  We stayed in a deluxe room on the second floor of the main building.  Our room had a full kitchen, dining set, fridge/freezer, and microwave.  We were happy with everything at the Eagle Inn.  When we arrived, we noticed how clean the room was.  

Overall, Santa Barbara hotel prices are high, but the Eagle Inn was reasonable.  Other hotels in the same area charged more, but looked older.
   
The location is two blocks from the beach in a quiet residential area.  It was a 10 minute walk to the wharf, and about 15 minutes walking to downtown.  The hotel has a private parking lot.  The lot was full in the evenings, but we were always able to find a parking spot.

The customer service was great.  The front desk was very efficient during both check-in and check-out.  All the employees were professional and friendly.

They have cookies and iced tea in the afternoon during check-in.  There is a library of DVDs that you can borrow from.  The free WIFI was nice.  The hot continental breakfast in the morning was good.  Each morning we got a bowl of fresh fruit, followed by either bagels and lox, yogurt with granola, or a hash brown bake with english muffin.  My favorite was the hash brown bake.

My wife was very happy with the Eagle Inn.  We enjoyed our stay and plan to return the next time we visit Santa Barbara.
Overpriced and not worth it. The greens inside my pita were very bitter and the falafel was bland. Schwarma on the go down the street is way better with similar food and cheaper prices.

I decided to stop and have a bite to eat while my kids were seeing a movie. I was sat immediately but...never greeted by a server. A couple that was sat after me (maybe 3-4 min) was greeted within seconds of being sat. Two servers and a food runner (?) walked past me. I turned and saw the host who sat me. Clearly I wasn't greeted as I had no drink and my menu was closed for some time. 

What a disappointing 1st time at this l

Wanted to update my review...The manager followed up with me a few days after I posted this. He was very nice and apologetic. He addressed his staff about my review. I look forward to going to Miller's Ale House again...

Excellent meal!
We sat outside and the atmosphere was wonderful...great place for a romantic dinner for 2.
Arrived around opening (17h) time, seeing we had no reservation, and that was good considering the place was hopping later.
Had a the taster's menu, which changes daily...as to b expected for the 8-course menu prepared by the chef himself, each dish was exquisite! Complimentary champagne, coffee and house granola for the road rounded of a lovely experience!
Staff in general were brilliant, but our waiter Paul deserves special mention...thanx.
They have lots of options. Employees are rude. Some things are wayyyyy overpriced. The fresh food in the back is great! I will return to get all my island ingredients. Fishy smell in the store

Thai lotus is AMAZING!!!

My boyfriend and I visited Thai lotus and had an incredible experience. Walking in, the restaurant was very clean and we were seated on a Friday night without reservation pretty quickly!

Our server was Nina and she was so great. Super quick, very attentive and funny! She checked on our table frequently throughout the night. 

I ordered the mango curry and it was so delicious. Mango curry is my favorite curry, but not many Thai places have it! I was very impressed with the dish. 

My bf ordered the salmon panang curry and it was also really good. The salmon was super soft and very tasty. 

We had left overs and they reheated very well!

The Thai tea was also really good! We are very impressed and will definitely be back!
It's always nice to fly with Alaska, they a friendly and easy to deal with. So glad they have a direct flight from rno to sna

I highly recommend Fast Feet Shoe Repair. They have put new heels on many of my shoes and they come back to me better than new! I recently brought my wedding shoes there to be dyed. They came out better than I expected!!! They are beautiful. They did such a good job. I am so pleased. The price was great and they were ready very quickly.
Don't go! My car was broken into yesterday and my computer and cell phone were stolen. Just avoid!

Cute place!

Our cheesesteaks and fries were good!

Breakfast here is good!

The options are great and everything I've had has been good, but the lines move very slow (so it takes up most of my lunch break to wait for them).  Secondarily, they are scheduled to be at my work one Wednesday a month and last month on their set day, they simply didin't show. No email, no notification, nothing. So obviously we had tons of frustrated people who were then forced to eat in our work cafeteria. Sadness ensued.

Four words: Fire Log Prime Ribs.

DO NOT FALL FOR "KOBE BEEF".  It is not at all what you would expect from anything you have ever heard about "kobe beef".

Price: 13.99 for regular week days.  More expansive on the weekends.

I am a long time Harrahs goer.  As a matter of fact, I only gamble at Harrahs when I am in Reno.  Carving buffet is the one that I used to always go to.  Aside from crappy comp points nowadays, Harrah's buffet has also really disappointed me in the past 2 trips.

Their selection is actually ok, they have less buffet counter than many other casinos, but other places repeat their selections over and over to fill up the counter.  King crab legs are just as salty as everyone else's.  Snow crab legs are kind of small, but acceptable.

Now prime ribs: MAN! How can you mess up prime ribs?  For the past two trips, both time they have only had well done prime ribs.  Yes well done though out! The whole thing! There were not "middle part that are more red", it is just one big chunk of fire log like thing that they somehow call "prime rib".  

An Asian chef was manning the carving station.  I waited for an hour and half, for that "next one" to come, only to see more completely well done prime ribs, and there were nothing the chef was willing to do to solve the problem.  Perhaps it was not his fault that he didn't understand what I was saying, but come on! It is called "carving buffet", so what about having an English speaking chef that knows how to cook prime ribs to man the "carving station"?  Would it be the least the buffet can do to keep up its name? 

And the Kobe beef they had, as advertise in front of the buffet.  It is nothing but a big chunk of beef shoulder roast.  It had nothing to do with the tender, melt in your mouth legendary Kobe Beef, just a big tough chuck of roasted beef.  I felt so scammed when I ate that thing, even though I somehow knew I shouldn't be expecting high grade Kobe beef with perfect marble distribution that melts in your mouth.  Still I have no idea why and how dare they call it Kobe beef.  I would have asked if the Asian chef understood English.

The good thing is that they had "cook to order" New York steaks.  And the lady was very nice and cooked everything according to my needs.  This earned them an extra star, along with my personal year of good memory I had with Harrah's Casino in the past.

Two months and my package Is not Delibery yet . And Now after almost two months This mail box Is requesting Permit of Import and export. This Is a Fraud No Human needs permit to send a small box . Also instead of Making a claim for not Delibery my package ,

About time for a deep cleaning...
This was my first time here and at first glance the place seemed inviting from the decor. As we were walking to pick a table it seemed we quickly needed a plan. Noticing above just about every table, the fans were loaded with dust with about an 1/2 inch to an inch hanging off. Two booths were vacant but still hadn't been cleaned yet and remained that way for about 15 minutes after we picked a table out that wasn't under a dusty fan. Looking down, the floors and bottoms of the booths were absolutely filthy. I will say the food was pretty good but with the front of the house in the condition that it was in, it definitely makes you wonder how clean the non-visible kitchen is....

I had such a great time at the little cat cafe! I am not usually around cats but I wanted to get familiar in case we decide to add to our family. Some of them were crazy precious! I wanted to adopt right away but unfortunately I was returning home that day and the rescue that they partmer with wasn't open.  

We opted for the treat bags and omg if you ever want to be surrounded by little furballs that is THE way to go lol in minutes I felt like the Pied Piper of Kitties!

The kittens were in quarantine because they had some sort of parasite (maybe ringworm??) But they still let you visit just make sure you wash your hands very thoroughly afterwards!

Would definitely go again next time I'm in Tucson!

I used to be fiercely loyal to chipotle but I have recently given qdoba a chance. This qdoba is super popular and there is usually a line but it moves fast. My standard order is a steak bowl with white rice, pico de gallo, corn, sour cream, cheese, lettuce and guac. I really don't like their queso, so I usually skip it. Overall it's pretty clean here and the employees are nice and friendly and always let me sample different meats!

Got a bit nervous for the first time riding the bolt bus and to make matters even worst; I lost my ticket along the way to the stop. The bus arrived as I turned my backpack upside down so I decided to just explain to the employee about this whole situation. Very friendly and helpful staff; checked my ID and got me on the bus before the standby crowds.
The AC was a bit strong as I heard girls sneezing.
Overall got to NYC an half hour late due to traffic.

Loved it! We had breakfast here today and it was great! It's so friendly and the food is great and so is the service! We put our name on the list and only waited about 20 minutes.  It's crowded and the locals eat here. The same folks that own this restaurant also own the restaurant at the end of the same strip mall Backwaters. We played Trivia pursuit while we waited for our meal. It's definitely a fun place!

We stopped here by chance on the way back (to Delaware) from AC, and absolutely loved it!  Best breakfast ever!  The service was great & this will definitely be "our place" whenever we're in the area.

Came here on a Saturday afternoon and was seated quickly. However, after being seated we waited 10 minutes to be greeted by a waitress and put in our order. Our 2 drinks came 10 minutes later and appetizer about 20 minutes. The food took about 45 minutes. I got the Baja tacos which wasn't very tasteful. The other person in the party got a half a chicken with a side of blood- chicken was not cooked.

I find that the menu is always a surprise and an adventure.  I love good food, wine and fantastic conversation.  This restaurant encourages the later by providing the former and that is hard to come by. This is a special place for friends and lovers that you want keep.  Share a fantastic evening with them at this very unique dining establishment.

I seriously love WFMCarrollwood. We'll plan our shopping trip on a late Saturday afternoon and stay for dinner. The food on the buffet line is outstanding. So many choices, ethnicities and tastes homemade! For a family of five, it costs almost as much as fast food without the guilt.  

As for the supermarket prices, it can tend to be a bit pricey, however, WFM excepts coupons and offers in-store coupons and specials.  Know your prices before you shop!  I love the variety of hard to find natural and organic foods.  The 365 store brand is fairly priced and a great substitution for expensive brand products.

Little pint-sized shopping carts are housed at the front of the supermarket.  My kids loving pushing their own carts and helping mommy shop for groceries.  WHF also offers children healthy snacks as part of their Kid's Club program.  In the cafe area, there is a hand-washing station and a children's play area.

As a service to the community, WFM also provides many healthy living workshops and fun tasting events.

I'm so happy I decided to give In Riva another try because it was far better!. I went on a Tuesday for half off pizzas which included the mushroom and zucchini pizza and the sausage and pepper both were amazing. Enjoyed the happy hour special on drinks and the staff was very friendly and attentive. I will be back !!

The food and service is exceptional, I've had food from here at all times of the the day at different points of the week and everyday is as good, if not better than the last. Food is great at all times of the day, my favorite is their brunch. If you're not afraid of good food at a reasonable price than try this out, you'll thank me later.

This was our first time here and it was awesome! Good pizza at a great price. This is the perfect lunch spot. 

We had the "two slice" lunch. It. Was fast, hot and good. We will be back!

We get to Nashville once or twice per year, and this is one of our favorite restaurants.  It's as good as it gets, even on a national basis for comparison.  The owner recognized us as we came in for dinner on a Friday evening, which is also a sign of competent management. 

While Lynn stuck with the saag paneer, I ventured to a (for me) new form of goat, called Goat karhai.. It was a stew, prepared very spicy, as I had ordered it.  Our meals also came with a very delicious achar and a tasty smooth raita.  We ordered roti and paretha aloo, respectively, for breads.  These are whole wheat and in the case of the "aloo", the bread is stuffed with potatoes.    I had a glass of wine and my wife Lynn had the excellent masala chai.

The next day, we returned for lunch and both opted for the buffet.   It was varied and excellent in taste.  WE both picked form the selection of vegetable and rice dishes, and had three different chicken preparations to select from.   There was also an unusual Yawa dish, which consists of a grain ball smothered with raita (yogurt).  For dessert, we selected ras mulai.  This dish is traditionally prepared with rosewater, which many Westerners are not familiar with.  The other treat was the the banana mango custard, which I hadn't seen elsewhere on Indian restaurant menus.  

If you are a serious fan of Indian food, you have to put this place on your circuit.  It would be hard to do better.  I only wish they had gajjah kuh halvah on their dessert menu.

We arrived without a reservation and upon approaching the hostesses, felt we were going to be turned away..but when seated, looked around and the place was nearly empty.  The waiters (young guys in an exceptional hurry it seemed) were on some kind of random rotation - there was no one specifically assigned to our table - and we quickly learned to ask for the same thing of maybe three or four of them to get whatever we wanted once.  Actually, it got funny after awhile, like it was a whack-a-mole game.  The fish was fantastic, and what we ordered, Cedar Plank Salmon, Grilled Rainbow Trout, Grilled Wild Bass, was all prepared tastefully, and interestingly, without any starch item.  So, we did not feel stuffed in the least.  The draft beers, though a limited selection, were great with the fish.  And the ending was certainly the crescendo of the meal.  The waiter threw the small thermal printout bill at our table, and then another guy ran by and just swept the bill and the credit card with an outstretched arm, without stopping!  We marveled at his dexterity!  Go for the food, and be entertained by some of the worst waiter service imaginable!

Oh Last Drop!

You are forever brimming with hipsters scrounging for wi-fi. Your coffee tastes slightly better than burned bottom boils.  Your pastries are overpriced yet there are millions of them.  The mosiac in the bathroom makes me vomit a little in my mouth. You insist on offering sub-par soy milk to put in the brown water you call coffee.

But...still...I love you. 

You manage to stay packed with countless Starbucks within a five-block radius.  You were the first coffee shop I ever came to in Philly (though I was not hip enough for you to give me a job). Your baristas play death metal at a coffee shop (hells yeah!) You provide me with a better wi-fi connection than I get at home. If you ever closed I'd have to rethink the meaning of life itself.

I ordered the lychee slush with mango bobs because I did not want to have any caffeine and I love lychee. 

This was very tasty.

My mom who has never tried lychee loved it and wanted to go back for a second. John also thoroughly enjoyed.

Yum yum

This place has the best God damned burger I've ever had. It was like greasy, delicious, bacon heaven. Get something on their Texas toast, holy shit, and don't plan on eating a light meal here. 

Absolutely fucking amazing. Keep it up Ernie's. If I die of diabetes because of your food, it won't be a life wasted.

I've been here about 4-5 times now I think and I am in love. I probably would come here once a week if I could. I've never had bad hair leaving the salon (I usually walk in with it looking like garbage) and it's so quick and cheap here. My hair never feels like it's stuffed with products. Everyone is super friendly and the online appointment booking and pay makes everything easier.
Went to see the musical Sunday. Menapause the Musical. The food was terrible. Very cold. Everyone said it was bad and cold. Room temperature at best. The Saturday crowd said the food was good.
D & L towing did a great job for me.  The driver Andrew was helpful and arrived quickly.  Highly recommend!!
Great fun! Fantastic beer! Excellent, knowledgeable and friendly staff! A visit is well worthwhile!
Gorgeous ambiance. It's a cute, dainty place. Very clean and the food is delicious & fresh. The service is great and everyone is very nice.

This was our first time here, even though for years we've heard great things about it.   Being as tonight is Valentine's, I was smart about it, thankfully, and made reservations. I'm so glad I did because the place was very busy. We were seated immediately, the waitress came right over and was happy to explain any of the dishes that we may have had questions about.  The food was delicious, the portions were decent sized, and the staff was all super friendly. Mind you, there was a little bit of a wait with getting our food and the check brought to us when we were done, but not a horrible wait, even though it was a full house. Our waitress bounced from table to table, keeping everyone's order correct and kept a smile on her face at each table. We were pleasantly surprised at how low our bill was for the two of us having the wonderful steak dinners that we did. We were very pleased with our first visit here and cannot wait to come back again.

First watch is one of my favorite breakfast spots. They have a very versatile menu and you really can't go wrong with anything you choose! I most recently tried the works omelet and the ingredients tasted very fresh. I appreciated how my takeout order was still hot & well prepared even though I wasn't dining in. The customer service was also great so I will be paying this place another visit. Highly recommend trying their seasonal items and their juices, they will not disappoint.

I came in a couple days ago to treat myself to a pedicure after a stressful day of work. I was immediately impressed with how beautiful and relaxing the atmosphere in the salon was, with calming music even playing in the background. The employees were very friendly and welcomed me with a smile. I had the deluxe pedicure which was SO incredibly amazing and Kim, the lady who did my pedi, was so kind and easy to talk to the entire time. Complimentary drinks are always a nice plus. This salon is very clean and will even make you your own tool box if you visit regularly. Everyone working there was so respectful and nice and made me feel valued as a customer. Not to mention how wonderfully soft my feet felt afterwards! I would highly recommend this salon and will definitely be back soon for a manicure!

Traci Berry is an excellent sales person for men,too. She has good experiences to add to your cycling background and ride. A big help to me in preparing for Katy Trail ride. She cares and takes time to serve.

She discovered a missing strap to my Timbuk2 bag that I purchased online. She called from store and tracked down my online order. They sent a new strap and I am using bag as Traci shows me. 

Store needs more stock, but still adequate. First rate service.

Conveniently located across from the recently-refurbished Highway Theater in Jenkintown, 211 is a small bistro-type restaurant with an emphasis on fairly traditional American cooking.  This is not to say that the food is boring, however.  Everything is delicious and many of the staff share a lineage that can be traced to George Perrier.  Chris the bartender is exceptionally talented and knowledgeable, and Tim, the owner and cook, is devoted to his craft.  Primarily populated by an older crowd, there is no reason to leave this unusually good suburban venue to them alone.  Oh yes, the shoestring potatoes are worth a visit by themselves.

Being a fellow resident from Maplewood, this business is very exciting for our community. The doughnuts are pretty good, the service is always friendly and unique, and the concept is fantastic. The owners have really worked hard to make this a "strange" experience. Our only constructive criticism is that the prices are a bit high for what you get and the shop is uncomfortably small during cold weather and busy times, but hey we are glad to see they are busy! It is wonderful to walk down the street at 9:00pm at night and see people lined up down the street to try these unique dones. Visit this wild and crazy donut shop for interesting and flavorful treats as well as a good cup of coffee.

This will be one of my favorite Thai restaurant in St Louis. The owners converted the place quite well from the previous Japanese restaurant. The inside appears more open and clean. Staff are friendly and attentive. Great selection  of Thai dishes and everything that we ordered has been very good so far. I would definitely recommend and come back.
Pharmacy is top notch.  Friendly knowledgable staff and pharmacist.  Fast curtious service.

As others have commented, I take my hair seriously.  If my hair doesn't look good, nothing else does.  Therefore, living 90 minutes away is not an imposition for me if the service is excellent.

First of all, the salon is beautiful, high end establishment.  The employees there have a tendency to take themselves a little too seriously, thinking that being aloof is synonoymous for upscale.  A smile and acknowlegment would be nice.  The line of hair products, Oribe to mention one, is fantastic.  I am a fan.  What I am not a fan of is that I feel, due to my demographic group, I was somewhat dismissed.

One appointment I waited over 30 minutes before the stylist came out and saw I was there.  I did, on several occassions try to catch the eye of the two receptionists behind the counter to no avail.  Also, I felt hurried through.  Even though highlights took forever (which is fine) the shampoo, base bump, and styling were rush.  Extra add-ons were put on my bill that I did not authorize, such as a Kerataise treatment for $30.00.  I still do not know when that took place unless it is similiar to a minute conditioner.

My bill on average was $200+, not including the tip.  The color was fantastic, the cut varied and it was never styled to my satisfaction with most of the time leaving the salon with it slightly damp.  My take is that their market is for the professional 20-30 age group.  While I am mildly satisfied, it is not worth the time (3 hours round trip), gasoline and expense.

As for the reference (in another post) about the massage chairs - they never were in working order.

This is the worst cleaning service that I have ever used.  The cleaners came back three different times and still did not do what was agreed upon in the estimate.  The fridge was to be completely disinfected and after 3 attempts there was still dried food particles left in the fridge.  All the bathrooms were to be disinfected and drawers and cabinents to be wiped out and after three attempts there was still hair in almost all the drawers in the bathroom.  We were hoping to get to move in to a clean and disinfected home and instead we wasted 280.00 on a cleaning service that did a horrible job!!!  I would definitely not reccomend this company for anyone in the Reno area!!!!!

Hadn't been here since last summer. Stopped in with my kids and some friends. It's a nice place to get some dessert.  Tried the drink with mango and custard, I usually will not order anything mango, but I'm glad I did. I recommend it it's not too sweet and it's so creamy and at the same time refreshing.  My kiddo had an ice cream sandwich that was as hard as a rock! Lol but she enjoyed it. The black and white shake is ok it's a vanilla and hot fudge shake.  I didn't like the watery consistency or the temperature of the shake thought hot fudge was a great idea... skip that. I like my shakes thick and cold. So... idk why I didn't take any pics ‍ sorry! Next time

Got sucked in by what I thought was a great sale. Paid in full for furniture and discovered 20 days later order had not been placed. The excuse was manager I worked with was terminated. It took 5 phone calls tp straighten things out to a point. I still have no delivery date. Can't keep blaming someone who is no longer there. Note that not one of my calls was returned.  I had to kerp calling to get any response. Recommend you drive on by despite what migh appear to be a great sale.
The food was great. Had the soft shell crabs and the bar scene is cool.

I've given this place two chances--no more.  The first time I went with my husband and our corned beef sandwiches were very dry,  The service was mediocre at best.  The second time I went alone.  There were only two others customers having coffee--it wasn't busy.  I ordered the pastrami reuben with fries and cole slaw.  The seasoned fries were great.  The sandwich was piled high with the fattiest, greasiest mess that I have ever seen--more fat than meat.  The bread was falling apart from the grease on the meat that soaked into the bread.  After my lunch was served I never saw the waiter again until I fianlly decided that eating that sandwich was impossible.  I had to get up and go to the check out counter and ask for my bill.  No one asked why I was leaving 90% of my lunch.

We stopped here for dinner as it was conveniently located across from Clearwater Beach... We should have kept on walking.. Service was terrible, Calamari was soggy, Shrimp Scampi was awful, Pizza was ok.  

Perfect looking tourist trap and they Got US!  lol

Best food we had in Santa Barbara!  Located next to the batting cage is this assuming taco restaurant. Tons of seafood options and great prices. Definitely a must try. Close to the zoo and Stearns wharf.

This is as good as it gets.  This is the Best McDonalds in St. Louis.  I've lived here for 20+ years and visited them all over the city and surrounding municipalities. Clean, Fast, and they do not skimp on product when you're ordering ice cream. I don't think they've ever messed up my order. Really nice people who seem to enjoy working together.

I have had this location and several others and this is the newest one I've attended. Sugar fire is going to cater our wedding next year and I would love to have the mac and cheese everyday. I've had all their meats and the brisket is definitely my favorite. I enjoy the soda options they have and the self service beverage station. If you haven't had the pickles they make, do it. Like tonight do it. 
The sauces! My favorite is the white sauce ( its like a horseradish bbq) and I coat that on everything. I like the sausage links with it the most! 
The french fries never disappoint either! 
My friend had a burger from there a couple of weeks ago and it was cooked perfect. Soo give them a try because I've had plenty from the menu and I haven't been disappointed yet!

I have lived near this restaurant for two years and never knew about them or ordered from them until tonight.  OMG  What was I missing!  The food is wonderful. I can't comment on the service because I had the food delivered by Order UP.  House of Yum is now on my favorite list!

They always charge more than prices posted on their website/menu then claim the website is out of date. Which has been going on for a while now. If you're a legitimate business you should post accurate pricing at all times.

Also they've made several mistakes with our take-out orders and then don't offer to make the situation right when you call back to make them aware of the mistakes. The employees don't have enough authority/autonomy from the owner(s) in these situations.

Do yourself a favor and head to the better Vietnamese spots in Chinatown or South Philly (or if you're into banh-mi's, Brown Street Coffee nearby has legit banh -mi's).

That being said, food is decent and it's the only Vietnamese spot around the neighborhood (aside from Brown Street coffee which only has banh-mi's)...
Great crabs always free n always excellent service. Try them out in fishtown. Hard to find though
Drove by today and there was a biker rally not social distancing and no masks. Wouldn't come here and support a business that fails to do there part.

i heard so many positive reviews about helena ave bakery but it fell short of my expectations. i came in on a saturday morning and shared the green bowl, the red bowl, and french toast with my boyfriend. i opted for the green bowl because i thought it would be a healthier option but it was drenched in dressing and super salty. the red bowl was good but nothing amazing. the french toast was the biggest disappointment. i'm not sure if it was a different type of french toast but it was very thick and not sweet at all. the service was okay; we had to clean our table ourselves as no one came to clean it. i don't think i'll be returning again given there are better brunch places around downtown santa barbara.

I came here the other day to get lunch with my friend, and let's just say I was very dissatisfied. First, the man serving us was not very polite and just seemed annoyed whenever we would ask for something. Once he dropped the food off, he never came back to check on us nor came by to refill our drinks. I could understand if he was busy but we were the only people in the entire place! Once we were done eating it took him 20 minutes to bring the check so we finally had to go up and ask for it. I put my card out right away and again took him forever to pick up the check so we had to go up and hand it to him ourselves. Bad bad service and I will not return!
Good food. Not a huge selection but what they have taste good. Great local atmosphere: hole in the wall feel. Definitely a locals place. It's tucked away so many people don't know about it.

We signed up for the cable tv, phone and internet service. The internet speed is great - often getting 50 MBs.

On the other hand there's the cable TV service. It seems like a lot of the channels I liked to watch on AT&T aren't there. The worst part of it is the software interface. Compared to AT&T it's like going from 2015 back to 1980. You can't record a show and watch it in any room, you have to watch on the particular device that records it. The fast forward function is hard to use, it seems either painfully slow, or so fast it flies past where you want to start watching again. Their programmers should look at AT&T's Uverse and copy it.

It was such a pleasure to work with John to make an engagement ring for my now fiance. I already had a diamond (family heirloom), so I was just looking for a setting. I had initially started my ring search at one of the larger chains (through a family recommendation), but then relocated to Jeweler's Row. I was very unfamiliar with the jewelers in that area, so I turned to Yelp for guidance and in doing so, found John's shop through all of the incredible reviews he had received.

The first time I walked into his shop, he was helping another couple design a custom setting. He gave me his card and asked me to return, but encouraged me to check out other shops in the area, which was surprisingly honest of him. He was so awesome to work with. I already had a pretty good idea of what my fiance wanted, and John helped bring it to reality. He never tried to push me one way or another, gave me plenty of time to come to a decision (3 visits before I gave him a deposit), and was just so nice and helpful (and knowledgeable) the entire time.

The ring itself was beautiful, and exactly what my fiance wanted. Also, it was incredibly affordable. It was a little too big (apparently I had the wrong ring size), but a week after I proposed, my fiance brought it to John and he resized it the same day. It now fits perfectly.

Overall, an amazing experience and we will definitely be back for our wedding bands. I would recommend John to anyone.
This rating is for  the grandma pizza specifically.  It's amazing. I don't like the other pizza as much. I only eat this and if you haven't had it I suggest u do if your in the area.

This is hands down the best pizza anywhere. Lucas the pizza maker outdoes himself every week! Thursday night is pizza night and by Friday morning I'm already looking forward to the next Thursday night. It's that good! I've recommended it to friends who all agree. We usually take ours home and give it a quick hit in a 410 degree oven... gives it that extra crisp on the crust (which is amazing by the way). The staff, including Lucas are all great, and very friendly. You've tried the rest now try the best!

I was really excited to check this place out! Unfortunately, I left Olio with a "meh" overall impression.

We showed up with a large group...BAD idea. They seated us outside their patio area, which was lovely. Nice décor and ambience. I selected a Riesling from the menu...and then waited. And waited. And waited. About 20 minutes later, my wine finally showed up. Then I asked for water...and waited. And waited. And waited. That took another 20 minutes to arrive.

Our waiter seemed to have a very difficult time with basic service. Half of us had to share utensils because we were never brought any (we had basically given up trying to ask for anything else).

The food--I had the chicken bruschetta. Excellent, though a tad overpriced. I also tried some of my friends' Turkish pizza, carrot salad, and King Louis crab bread. Delicious! Our waiter was so confused with the orders, we ended up with extra food. Fantastic for us, probably not so great for business.

I may come back, but it will probably be awhile, and certainly not with a big group.
Repeat customer. If your looking for great product and service Tint King is the place. They are always fast and friendly, my windows look great and help keep my car cooler!

I had my Birthday celebration there Friday night and was beyond impressed with the whole experience.

It was a large party but they were more than accommodating for the 12 of us. Valet parking was only $3 but they do have a lot as well. 

We enjoyed the chefs cheese selection which various types of cheeses including hard, soft, blue, etc....I also ordered the pumpkin which came with a curry type sauce and was delicious. I looked at the menu ahead of time and knew I wanted the "Loco Moco" a perfectly cooked beef patty on top of rice and an over easy egg on top and did not disappoint. 

I highly recommend David! He is clearly an experienced server, very knowledgeable and very attentive.

I have been aware of this place since before it opened. I haven't visited because I wanted to save it for a rainy day. I knew that once I went, I would never be the same. And I was right. I have actually already applied for a job there. I need to be in this space with these magical creatures. 

I was walking by just as it opened and thought this was as good a time as any to stop the madness. My first impression was how clean and organized everything was. The cafe area was top notch and cozy, with cat paraphernalia galore. There are yummy snacks to nosh on and the drinks are no joke. There is quality coffee (I had a Caramel Macchiato), designer tea (I had a chai latte), and even smoothies (I LOVED the mango). They even bother to make little designs in the foam...I had a flower and a cat paw of cinnamon. Very clever touch. The drinks are unlimited so bottoms up! Some people may scoff at the $15 price tag for an hour with the cats, but it's pretty much free it if you have three $5 drinks. 

The real danger here are the cats. You will be hard pressed not to adopt one. I am not joking. I almost walked out with Penny, the little white one with yellow eyes who stole my heart. I almost cried when I had to leave her. If you have a little kid, good luck with getting out without a new pet. Don't go here unless you are looking to adopt a cat or risk the wrath of your child.

These cats are seriously adorable and in every personality. They are some of the most well behaved and lovable felines I have met. They are fine with kids, even the little ones who can be less than gentle. They are active and playful and mostly polite. Sometimes they even fetch their toys and bring them to you to play. It's darling!

I love that there is an area for small children and one that is for only 7 years and up. I was pleasantly surprised that the kittens bounded right down there with the children to play with them. These are not scaredy cats at all which means they are probably going to make wonderful forever pets. 

I love that the cafe has already adopted out over 100 cats since they opened a year ago. This place is really doing our community a service by supporting SAFE team which is a no kill organization aimed at educating the public and saving animals lives.

If you have any love of cats, you need to check this place out. With any luck, maybe it will be me serving you your paw print cinnamon dusted drink.

Tower Hill is an amazing brewery hidden in an unassuming shopping center! Beer being brewed in vats right next to the bar, great tasting beer, bartender was attentive and provided a sample at request. Heard the food is amazing too, will definitely visit again

This place downtown has been the best by far in Tucson that we have visited. My husband and me rode our bikes from north to downtown. The quesdilla was OK the chicken was a bit dry. But my husband's tacos were awesome. The guacamole was amazing. The salsa bar with chips is just fabulous. Real salsa and house chips. Fast service and very clean place (even the bathroom). My husband enjoyed the choices of beer on tap while there. We have to go back for happy hour.
Wings are excellent!! Onions are unbelievable. Great lunch specials everyday 11:30-3pm. Love the bar too. Cannot wait for the Wynnewood location!
Lines were long and it took a long time to get two ice teas.  One ice tea came and the other too another 5 mins.
Some of the worst food I've ever had. The wings actually tasted like fish. They were, without a doubt, the worst wings I have ever had. The pizza was a 2.5 out of 5 at best.

Who doesn't love a place where you can walk in and grab a giant gooey warm cookie? Or get it topped with some ice cream and other crap that's extremely bad for you but over-the-top delicious?

Love it here.

Local favorite.  Weekend is full house during breakfast and lunch hours. The service is good and price is friendly.  I ordered the simple breakfast dishes and came out great. If you are here on St Patty's Day, will use real corned beef instead of canned for the corned beef hash.

We have two large Newfoundland dogs and buy their grooming supplies at the Pet Edge Reno location. When it comes to big dogs with heavy coats a small bottle of grooming product just isn't going to go far and we like the idea we can buy the gallon size containers and not have to pay expensive shipping for these purchases. I would like to also say that the service we have received has been excellent. It is nothing such as described in one of the reviews on this site. The employees that work there have always treated us like first rate customers even though our business does not even come close to the business I'm sure they get from the local grooming shops. We consider ourselves very lucky that we have a Pet Edge distribution warehouse within driving distance of us and that we can pay wholesale prices. So my husband, dogs, and I all would all like to say that we really appreciate both Pet Edge and their employees.

Absolutely delicious! Better than Din Tai Fung. Mama Wong's dumplings, fried rice, Crystal shrimp, veggies, chicken wings were phenomenal. I highly recommend eating here to satisfy your dumpling and Chinese food cravings. The service was great, there's easy parking at the shopping center and the restaurant was very clean.

Got a take out dinner. Ribs were smoked, good & sauced. Nice 6-7 ribs for a dinner. The side of collards was excellent, not the best collards I've ever had, but they were cleaned, well seasoned and cooked to perfection. The RIBS were great, and the French fries were cooked perfectly. I can not comment on their service, but the waitresses were the ones doing the take outs. They cared, what more can I say ? They wanted me to have a good experience 
I would definitely go back, no reason not too

We stopped by for lunch without checking the ratings. Our mistake. Cajun specialities, but the prices are way out of line (nearly $15 for an oyster po-boy???) and the quality of the food was just a notch above so-so. Add to this the fact that we couldn't get an Abita beer. In New Orleans??? Maybe we've overlooked something, but we suggest you pass on the Cabin and keep walking down Bourbon Street.

Tasty! Definitely not bar food. Italian beef sandwich was flavorful and tender. Fried pork chops were juicy and perfect amount of breading. Onion rings were bite sized and not over breaded. I had the black and blue salad special for lunch. The salad dressing was really good. The meat was seasoned nicely. They were quite busy for lunch.
the food here is great!! salads are made fresh, not put in fridge overnight n the baked ziti n burgers r so delicious too!!

Just go here! I was traveling through St. Pete's and initially stopped for a smoothie, but after hearing the woman next to me in line rave about the buffalo tempeh sandwich, golden milk soft serve, and cheesecake with banana bread, ended up trying those too. The food was all delicious, all vegan and gluten-free, and the staff was exceptionally friendly and accommodating. If I'm ever in the area again, I'll definitely be back to Love Food Central.

Damn fine place for food and beer! As soon as I walked in it had this very casual/laid back feel to it, but still felt classy. Our server was a friendly guy and was able to answer our questions on the menu. They have a great bottle list and a decent tap list, also tons of good whiskey. The food was very good, and I am glad I gotten to eat here. The crispy pig ears wit the aioli was amazing and my Red Drum was so good with that great crispy skin! I defiantly would love to return here for dinner and have some whiskey cocktails!
We were pleasantly surprised with this place! Great service, fantastic food, and VERY strong Aquaritas! Our server, Ashley was personable and made great recommendations.
Amazing sushi. Incredible quality. Innovative menu. Great staff! Ive tried everything. The wasabi salmon bowl is a must

Ordered takeout and this is just horrendous. I would have happily paid more for better ingredients. The taste is subpar, the eggs were cheap and rubbery tasting. 
I ordered a breakfast sandwich with eggs and paid extra for ham. I'm happy they forgot it because I wonder about the quality after trying one half of the sandwich. 
How is one whole sandwich served with different scrambled eggs? One half is yellow and looks fine, the other is green and clearly has mold spots. Pepper is obvious and those are not black pepper spots. 
I don't recommend this place because eggs are an easy dish you can't mess up, yet they did. 
If your staff doesn't care about what they're cooking, considering all one has to do is look, why bother eating anything else?

Went here on a Saturday night after a wedding which I was in town for.  The Vanderbilt crowd which I hung out with the Thursday prior highly recommended Robert's so I'm glad our party wound up stopping in.   We got there sometime after 10pm and the place was hopping.   The honky tonk, Johnny Cash sounding band was excellent and exactly the sort of thing you're looking for when in Nashville. It was very loud and crowded but not so much as to impose on the fun.  People-wise, there seemed to be a little bit of everything (good people watching, I even saw Abe Lincoln!) and fun to hang out with!  I just drank Corona so I can't really attest to the drinks at the bar but the service was timely and friendly.  Definitely check this place out!

I recently moved here from Boston and am a foodie.  I am a big fan of Commanders Palace and have eaten there over 20 times with not one disappointment.  We went there the night before and decided that we would try another place.  I had read great reviews about Restaurant August and planned to go there for my 50th wedding anniversary.  What a disaster.  The food was inedible.  I ordered lamb only to find out it was done in vinegar.  It was terrible.  Not to be outdone my wife ordered octopus and it was also done with some type of vinegar sauce.  My daughter who is also an excellent cook was extremely disappointed with her fish dish.  The portions are small and I don't have a problem with that but the three of us did not finish our meals.

Listen I know that most of the world can't deliver food the way that St. Barts does.
To me one of the key things of having a good restaurant is to have good recipes.  I have never cooked or served either lamb or octopus in a vinegar sauce.  

To top it off we had a waitress who was trying to be the next Bob Hope; she very annoying and had inappropriate comments throughout the evening.  For example when my wife and daughter
went to the rest room the waitress come buy to tell myself and the gentlemen with me that we shouldn't steal the desserts from the women when they were away from the table.

The desserts,however, were A+ and the ambiance of the room was magnificent.  The gentlemen who was overseeing the dining room was outstanding and a gentlemen.

It turned out to be one of the most embarrassing eating experiences of my life and when it's on your 50th wedding anniversary it made it even worse.

Ok I know pizza!! I've eaten at tons of Brick Oven/Wood Fired style pizzerias. If Bavaro's wants to remain in Tampa then they need to get it right. Yesterday I stopped in for lunch and ordered the Arugula personal pie. It came to my table soggy and the toppings fell off when I picked it up. Zero flavor. Not what I was expecting. Perhaps RE-Training needs to take place here on how to properly make a Neapolitan Wood Fired Pizza.  Hope it's not like this at the other locations.

Wow!! Great addition to the hood!
My girlfriend and I had our first meal there at 5 pm yesterday, and loved it. We ordered 4 dishes, a total of about $33($40 with a tip), and had a little trouble finishing everything and licking the plates. "I could eat 2 green papaya salads myself" was my thought.
The large chicken pho came piping hot with a bunch of mung bean sprouts, a bouquet of basil and 1/2 a lime on the side. Next time, I'd get even more sprouts. So good. 
The Shrimp Summer Rolls and sweet peanut dressing were delicious.  The Broken Rice/Chargrilled Pork looked like it would be our least favorite but was incredibly tasty. My friend who'd live in Thailand near the Vietnam border thought the rice was cooked perfectly. 
Service -now this was late afternoon- was congenial, quick and sensitive, with 3 different waitstaff tending to us-without hovering. Since the food is so tasty, the price is right, and it's a new business, it's understandable that at rush hour, things could get hectic. Our solution, until the minor popularity kinks get ironed out, is to just eat early or not during peak hours. Hey, popularity has a price!

lovely spot for lunch in the city! super casual and great atmosphere to catch up with your crew!  the menu has a variety of munchies and typically come in small plates.  i tired the cauliflower, pizza, caesar salad and ricotta toast.  i enjoyed almost everything but keep in mind they do offer smaller plates so it might not be enough to share. the only disappointing thing was the caesar salad which was not memorable nor was it enough to satisfy the lunch appetite lol 

the pizza was better than what i expected! i never knew di bruno bros is known for pizza? but that's a solid choice whether it's for lunch or dinner.

i will def return for some light bites and maybe a glass of wine or cocktail.  worth checking out if you haven't been yet!

The office has moved to a new location on Linebaugh, just east of the former location. 

Dr Wetzger has left and I have been seeing Dr Tanuja Sharma for over 3 years. 

I'm so blessed. She's even better than Dr. W.

She is caring and loves her profession. She listens, and takes time with her patients. She knows her professional and treats her patients with dignity. 

I'm so lucky to have such a great PCP. 

Highly recommend. TGH what an asset you have in Dr Sharma. She is a gem, and more so a great doctor. A credit to her profession.

Well, I think this a ideal spot for Outback Steakhouse. I was able to park right away & get seated really fast.  Valet parking is available. Great staff & management. For the appetizer, I the coconut shrimp which was good & cooked just right.  For dinner, I ordered steak & grilled shrimp on the barbie. The medium well steak was cooked excellent. The shrimp was nicely cooked.   My sides was sweet potato & mixed vegetables was good good as well.  The restaurant itself was beautiful.  I will be back.

As a huge fan of libraries I was pretty disappointed by this new branch. I read that the library cost $16 mil to build, and yet everything inside seems so cheap. The furniture is cold plastic, the floor boards squeak loudly. There's not enough quiet space for reading/studying/working. It's a disaster.

One thing I will say in favor of this place is that they do have a lot of power outlets...so if they were to get comfy furniture people could bring their laptops.

What's the deal with the parking lot entrance too? Four lefts to get in?! 
I'm sticking with my Weber Road branch and quietly missing Tesson Ferry.

Thought I would post a review since they remodeled and revamped the menu. I have to say, I am impressed. I've been going here for years because I'm dedicated to buying local, but I agreed with past reviewers on certain negative issues. Since they redid the café it's a lot cleaner cut (although I would have described it as "earthy" but never "dirty"). Someone made a comment about the bathroom a while ago, but that has also been remodeled. 

The new menu is pretty good, and I like that the sandwiches come with a side salad (which is really good--no iceberg lettuce here!) instead of chips. Nothing that knocks me off my feet, but it's not bad if you're there all evening to study. 

It's definitely NOT an in and out type place. The coffee takes a lot longer than Starbucks, but it much higher quality. It's great for a relaxing afternoon or a study session; it's the wrong place for a quick bite to go. The owner even gave me trouble (in a light hearted way) once for asking for a to go cup because "The French don't drink coffee to go" which made me smile and he was really nice about it.  

If you come here with the intent to actually enjoy your coffee you won't be disappointed!!

BFF and I researched before deciding on Waldorf. We booked the entire day with a treatment, massage, facial, and blow out.  To be fair, my massage was amazing but my best friends was terrible.  He massaged or rather touched with one hand, didn't do a deep tissue as requested, nor did he actually do the exfoliating scrub the way advertised. When we expressed our concerns, the manager separates us so that she could talk to my best friend, which really angered her since she is a little more reserved and didnt want to make the person feel bad. The manager agreed to refund me for her treatment and massage, when we checked out later, they had only refunded one treatment.  When I asked the front desk what had happened, they told me I had to come back since the manager had left for the day. You could tell the person at the front desk just wanted to leave (it was right before closing). We were there just for the weekend, and we decided to not go back and deal with the negativity.  For the amount of money you pay for here, you would expect consistent great service. honestly, i would go elsewhere..there are other places in NOLA that will treat you better.

I have been to Sly's for dinner a few times and it is a fun place to stop for a cocktail and some appetizers. The drinks and starters are always great, but for the price of the entrees the quality is hit or miss.

Just wow, just... WOW. Good food, Good cheesesteak! Please come here, good chicken fingers. good fries. The honey mustard, eh, it's ok, didn't like it to much, but it's good! They were very, very nice people. Just come here, you'll have the time of your life, please trust me on this, you'll love this place, eat or miss out, like I said please come here!
There were five tables occupied when we entered; we made six.  We ordered wings and potato skins.  Forty five minutes later, no food.  We walked out.  Things that make you go hmmmmm...

My favorite is the catfish tacos or the redneck tacos but you can't go wrong with the ribs. Man I wish they would come up with some sort of fresh corn side dish. I'm pretty picky about my sides and I like my veggies fresh. Would love to see some fresh summer veggies and maybe some squash dishes in the winter. One of a kind type sides.

Rev Tony and his wife are nice people but there were a number of issues that cannot be overlooked.  I provided sample pictures and information regarding my wedding bouquet and informed Rev Tony exactly what I wanted but when I called a few days later to check on the bouquet, Rev Tony informed me the bouquet had not been ordered and it was only 2 days before the wedding.  When I arrived at the venue for the ceremony, the flowers on the bouquet were wilted.   The flowers looked as though they were made the day before and no one placed them in water to keep them fresh.  The day before the ceremony I called Rev Tony to go over the vows and I forwarded a copy via email of what would be said at the ceremony but he forgot to print out what I sent him so that he had it with him for the ceremony.   I informed Rev Tony the day before the wedding that my husband and I would have something to say to each other during the ceremony but Rev Tony forgot about it and began to pronounce us husband and wife and I had to stop him to remind him that we had planned to say something to each other.  At the end of the ceremony, Rev Tony presented me with a credit card receipt to sign which I thought was really tacky and the charges for the wilted flowers had a cost higher than what was discussed and agreed to.  The total cost to simply arrive at the park to officiate the wedding and to present me with wilted flowers was too high.  I could have paid a minister a couple of hundred dollars to officiate our wedding and arranged for my own flowers.
