Rev Tony on several occasions talked about the French Quarter Wedding Chapel's plans to ensure we had a "beautiful" wedding but I am still trying to figure out what he did or what was he suppose to do to make that happen.  A lot of talk but no substance.

Usually go to Mimi's for breakfast, but went tonight for a school charity event.  Love the dinner menu - so much variety it took a while to decide.  Do yourself a favor and order the sweet potato fries.  Yes they are 99 cents more but so worth it - Yum!  Shout out to our server Rachel & actually all wait staff are great here :)

I would give six stars if I could! Liz shot my wedding and engagement photos and I absolutely couldn't have asked for anything more amazing. She's the best! She's professional, creative, and an absolute pleasure to work with.

Amazing customer service! Linda takes the time to get to know her customers. She was happy to see me, and even required about my sister who was with me on my last visit. My glasses had literally been crushed by a school bus and she ordered the replacement pair with no hesitation. LensCrafters really should be Linda's place, cause if she ever leaves it will never be the same!

A great wee spot on whyte to grab a coffee and/or a gelato. For once in a review I'll say that it's reasonably priced! 

The they give you a (n)ice big scoop of gelato and the coffee is grand. 

Added perks are the free wifi and the "take a book, leave a book" library.

Food halls are very uncommon in Florida, so it was nice to come across this one in Tampa. 

Overall, the parking lot is huge. I didn't have any trouble finding parking. The food hall has several restaurants to choose from. I was honestly surprised to see how big it was! The place is perfect for date night vibes or hang out vibes with friends. 

We tried food from quite a number of the restaurants. Everything was good but a little on the pricier side. I'd definitely be willing to come back another time I'm in town to try out other restaurants!

Love this place. A group of us come here every Thursday night and seem to get the best service. Bayardo the manager is awesome. Vanessa is such a great waitress. Overall, a very enjoyable experience every time.

We went on a private wine tour with my girlfriends for my 40th birthday.  We were 8 ladies, and Shawn was our tourguide.  He was fantastic. We had a great time on the tour. Sogno del Fiore was our favorite stop followed closely by Standing Sun! We tasted great wine, loved all the information Shawn provided. He was very patient and wonderful with 8 ladies with all kinds of requests :) We had a blast !  Setting up the tour was easy. Shawn was very responsive to my emails/questions and very accommodating in our requests. I would definitely do another tour with them if I have a chance.  Recommend it completely to anyone who is interested in the Santa Barbara/Santa Ynez wine region.  Definitely worth it!!!!

The definition of my go to eat/drink/hang spot on Magazine st. With their delicious margaritas (I recommend on the rocks), massive nachos, and flavorful cauliflower tacos, Rum House never disappoints. A sure favorite for every ravishingly hunger customer is their Taco Trifecta combo (3 tacos and one side) for $15. With vegetarian and pescatarian options for tacos, all will be satisfied. My clubs at school used to always cater Rum House (pre-COVID) and their fried plantains and sweet potato fries were always a crowd favorite (and my personal favorites). 

They have ample outdoor seating in the shade (you may have to wait on a weekend night, but otherwise should be a-ok to find a spot as a walk-in). 

I never have a problem parking on Ninth street (free), they also have reasonable prices and a young and kind staff.

BY FAR MY FAVORITE PLACE TO EAT IN PINELLAS COUNTY!!! The combination of flavor, presentation, and hospitality are like non other! Jamie, the manager, is very genuine and knowledgeable of the menu! Chef Justin Murphy is amazing! Can't say enough great things about this restaurant! DO YOURSELF AND FAVOR AND ENJOY THIS EXP

Very good service. The employees are all very professional and actually show you the filters when they remove so you can see. The car wash was well done and they took time to make sure it was done right. It may take longer than others but it's cause there doing it right.

My second or third visit in perhaps ten years.  As for the quality of the food I'd give a rating of 4.  I had a delicious Bearclaw heated up in their self-serve microwave with tub butter (hard as a rock right out of the freezer), an egg- over-hard/cheese/bacon Breakfast Sandwich on Ciabatta (tasty but a half sandwich at best), & a cup of dark-roasted reg. Coffee (loaded it up w/ 8 raw sugar packets & Half n' Half.  All of this was satisfying though a bit pricey.

My displeasure came in the form of the place's layout.  Whether in the Time of covid-19  or not, what sense does it make to have one(1) 6'+/- counter for EVERYONE to converge on for coffee, creamer, sugar, & microwave.  I had flashbacks to WDW (Walt Disney World) where coffee/tea drinkers would be LINED-UP insufferably behind some nincompoop mixing their creamer, sugar, whatever at the counter while others wait impatiently behind them.  

THEN, TO MAKE MATTERS EVEN WORSE, there were diners plowing their way into the middle part of the "very small" counter to get to the microwave on the underneath shelf.  WTF!  By the way, butter, flatware, ice, sodas, etc is all at the opposite end of the dining room.  Thus, one gets to go ALL OVER the place to complete their meal.

OK, we ate outside on a cool but sunny morning in February, acceptably distant from other diners, so in spite of the infuriating beverage/condiments/utensils layout, it ended up being pleasant.

We called five plumbers and they couldn't check our water heater for two weeks. Called Straight Up Plumbing and he was at our house in two hours. He assessed the situation. Diagnosed the problem and got to work immediately. Honest and straight forward. Good price. Cost the same as what we paid foe a similar repair ten years ago. The new water is running great.

Yes, there is a drive-in theater in the St. Louis area. It's old school... well, not as old school. Instead of hanging a speaker on the side of the car, you can tune into a dedicated AM station.  Just make sure your speakers are working in your car.
 The concession stand is kind of ghetto, in my opinion. There's the fake cheese, nachos, popcorn, and hot dogs, all a little overpriced, but you fell like you're walking in a grade school cafeteria line.
 Stereotypically, drive-ins are make out spots, and it's kind of funny to smirk at "steamed up windows." I didn't know that happened, but it does here.
 It's not stadium seating, but it's a good place to experience some childhood nostalgia, or gain a new experience. Fun stuff... I suggest trying this place out before they ALL close down.
Outstanding service! Very nice people. They rescued our favorite kitchen clock.

I so wanted to like this place since I live right up the street.   But after ordering take-out a couple of time and being disappointed,  I'm not sure I'm going to go back for a while.   I was excited about the fried chicken and the pot pie and both failed to impress.

I will keep this brief, like my 35 minute dinner at Paesano's.

The staff made me laugh. They treated me like a loyal long time customer or a friend, even though it was my first time.

The sandwich (the Paesano) was incredible. I cannot believe I ate all of it, but it was too delicious not to.

The Tuscan fries (shared by our table of 3) were a perfect complement to the sandwich.

I drank a Fresca. Thank you, Paesano's, for having Fresca.

Remember to bring cash.

Make sure your table has napkins. You will need them.

Appreciate the greasy goodness. 

That is all.

One of the best! We went here around Christmas. I had the fried chicken and it was so good, spicy with something like pepper jelly glaze. (doesn't look like it's on the menu right now! I'd be so disappointed!) I also had the cornbread and it was awesome, I even took some home. They have a great wine list and the restaurant is SO beautiful with great service.

Subway Sandwich are much better.

This place is not clean and maintained. The employees working here do not care for customer's order and they do not pay attention to the order. Especially when it is only to go order - they should be very careful to the order. It is very upsetting to find out that your whole order is messed up and it is not eatable! You wasted your lunch or dinner plan and money.

The quality of the ingredients used is very low level and get you sick.

When you go there notice the appearance and cleanliness of the place - it is bad.

I would never go here and I would not recommend this place at anyone else.

This is the only Costco I've been to that isn't a complete madhouse on the weekend. I've only been on Saturdays and Sundays and it's not dead but not crazy busy. 

My love for Costco has no bounds. Where else can I skip lunch and instead fill up on free samples? Where else can I stock my toilet paper supply for the next 3 months? Where else can I get a footlong hot dog and soda for $1.50 (this price hasn't changed in 20+ years and that makes me happy). It's well worth the $50/year membership fee once you add up the savings. 

Their meat section is phenomenal and you can't beat the prices. You'll find wine for much less than in the grocery store (can't beat $7.99 for Mark West Pinot Noir). And no trip to Costco is complete without grabbing a deliciously moist $4.99 rotisserie chicken. 

But be warned: it's easy to get carried away. You will find everything you need here (in three times the size you'd normally find it) as well as plenty of tempting impulse buys. It's like Target on steroids.

This was the first visit to the Mellow Mushroom.  I was pleased with the extensive menu choices.  Not just your average pizza.  Our pizza came out slightly wrong, but the waitress was quick to spot it, and get a new one in right away.  We ended up with a ton of leftovers due to the extra pizza, which I will gladly consume!  The pizza was really good!  I also noticed a "frequent diner" discount on my bill (which I'm obviously not, yet) which was maybe for the mix-up?  In any event, the pizza was great, the service nice and attentive, and it ended up being super cheap.  We'll be back.

The fast-food version of Carrabba's Italian Grille has the same good food, albeit the wedding soup is too salty to eat. Service, limited as it is when you order from a counter and pour your own drinks, was excellent. Food is prepared fresh and quick. They do have a wine bar. Don't care for the deli like atmosphere, and the nearly same prices as Carrabba's. Lots of people in the dining room so it must be profitable.

I recently moved from LA looking for a good nail shop and I ran into this one while shopping on State St. When I first started coming I realized that they were extremely expensive but I automatically thought I was paying for the area so I was okay with it. I wore long nails at the time so I was paying about $65 every two weeks. I started noticing my nails breaking so I thought they were because my nail bed was so small. The last two times i've been here I noticed that my gel has been peeling. The first time I automatically thought it could be me but I realized it wasn't so I came in today expecting to get a fill and tell them what was happening but I received NOTHING! (no apology nothing) The lady seemed to have an attitude and even questioned how many times I have came. The customer service here is trash! I will never spend another dime here again.
Blackened Grouper and garlic fries...find this place, it's well worth it. Not for Applebee lovers, this is for folks who enjoy a true neighborhood restaurant.

OMG!!! I ordered for a party over Labor Day. I had meat eaters, vegetarians, vegans and kids coming! Frank and Gus were super helpful in selecting the menu, answered my endless questions and helped me plan a great part menu. If that weren't enough... the food was fantastic! Everyone at the party commented on how awesome it was! I will always use them in the future and recommend them to everyone!!! Thanks Frank and Gus!!! You guys are awesome!!!

Marx was awesome! Professional and friendly. Diagnosed our tree problem at the free estimate, told us that they don't handle these type of problems and recommended another professional. If I ever need pruning, etc...I kept his card and will call him!!
Very quick to get our food so minimal exposure to others. All staff wearing masks. Delicious food always!

The novelty of watching a fresh donut be consummated, born and then dressed up for adoption wears off after one visit. Do they taste good? Yes. (Find me fried dough that *doesn't* taste good and I'll give you a proper "well, damn!" gif).  However, the yummy factor can't outweigh the timeliness factor in the long run. This is the northeast folks. We want things made quickly. Also, they are limited by one basic cake donut at its core. You can't get a Boston cream. No jelly donuts, either. What about a chocolate frosted chocolate cake donut? Nope.  I actually prefer dunkin donuts (sorry, Duck). I have a feeling this place will close after all the buzz dies down.

Love illegal petes!  Their breakfast bowls and burritos are awesome. The chili sauce is so good. Decent price. The lunch atmosphere is fun the loft upstairs is pretty cool. I am a bigger fan of their breakfast than their lunch but haven't had any complaints and the management is really nice and cool.

This food was absolutely horrible I have eaten from this one many years ago and I did not like it then I tried the one in Sparks loved it!! ordered food today from this one not only did the driver shake half of my food down in the bag but the Al Pastor looks like they used food coloring just to make it change colors no flavor the tortillas appear to have been dipped in vegetable oil but never cooked the Carna Asada tasted like boiled beef with cilantro this was a very horrible experience I never liked this location and never will
Dark, old beautiful. Great place to get a drink with the person you love. And the best Sazerac's.

A little over a year ago (Super Bowl Sunday 2008, to be exact), I first visited the Sports Attic and what a visit it was. I ate all the chili and hot dogs I desired - wait for it .......... for free. I won an autographed football during a raffle, embarrassed myself upon receiving it by incorrectly identifying the Hall of Famer whose signature adorned the ball, and promptly sold the ball before exiting to pay for my bar tab (free food and free beverage - what a time). And most importantly, I witnessed, for the first time in my life, an of-age patron order an O'Doul's. Amazing. 

So, when it came time for this year's clash of the titans, I knew exactly where to go. With an even larger group, I returned for the Super Bowl, 2009 edition, to find that, even in our crumbling economy, free hot dogs and chili were still to be had. A few buckets of beer and my very first taste of wings later, wouldn't you know it, I won yet another raffle. I'm also pretty sure that I fell in love with the tall, blonde waitress in the skintight referee's uniform, but alas, it was fleeting. 

Yes, my experiences were grand. But really, this is a pretty average place. There are plenty of TVs for athletic event-watching, but one is always a couple of seconds ahead of all the others and the sound. A bucket of A-B products and a 2 lb. plate of wings that seems to vary in size from table to table will run you $20, so take that for what it's worth. And truth be told, one does end up paying for the free food in the end. But this really is a hidden gem for events such as the Super Bowl. The staff seems to work hard to keep the atmosphere light and the fun flowing. 

So, will I return? Every Super Bowl that I am still in St. Louis for. And I suggest you all do the same.

A few surprises!
Honestly, I was surprised by number of Sushi chefs in the small space...and sushi itself was not as bad as some sushi restaurants. Portion is normal size and price is...I think it is good price...except "Rice is too soft." Rolls are...well, a few variety and, by standard for take-out sushi, acceptable for non-Japanese place. One finding...they sell whole block (saku) of Tuna if you are going to make Tuna sushi or Sashimi.

The BEST shrimp and grits I have ever had!! The crab cakes are phenomenal as well!!
They have a great happy hour special and the owner is such a sweetheart!! 

Also, a portion of all of their proceeds is donated to a local autism-support entity!! Great food with an amazing cause!! Definitely a new favorite place for me!! :)

After my first visit to J Sima Salon, I can say Marco is truly great at what he does. I came in with a very specific vision for my hair, and he worked with me until it was achieved, and never made me feel like I was being annoying (even though I totally was). Thanks for the greatest color and cut (and a great temperament), Marco!
Kailys are the real pros. Quick estimate, scheduling, and tree gone. You'll hardly know they were there. Pricing was good too. Call these folks and you'll be happy you did.

I bring all my vehicles to this discount tires. The whole team is very helpful. Ive probably been helped by every one of them. These guys are on their game 24/7. This business has secured my future business. Thanks again. Also close to many different restaurants, you can grab a decent bite to eat while discount tires do their thing. Also forgot to add b4 you even get out of your vehicle outside you are greeted by some one. As a business owner myself i can tell you these guys are excellent.

4.5 stars...

I went to both Clearwater and St Pete/Pass-A-Grille beaches while in Florida and found both to be quite similar. The beaches are wide though if you're going during low tide more than half the beach is moist and packed down and you'll be farther from the calm clear waters if you want to sit in the soft white sand. Everyone talks about how white the sand is at Siesta Key and although it is the whitest sand, the sand at the rest of the beaches in the area don't vary a great deal and are still very nice. St Pete beach is a longer beach and if you keep going south you'll reach Pass-A-Grill which is much less busy (it's mostly residential) but there's still a nice concentration of restaurants/shops on 8th ave (otherwise the shops at St Pete can be spread out a bit). Clearwater's slightly smaller beach makes for a little denser business concentration and they do have pier 60 which is cool to check out or go fishing on (for a small fee). If you're debating between the two there really isn't a huge difference. There are nice beach bars at both, same great sunset, same great soft sand, and you have to pay for parking and leave your alcohol at home (or of course get creative with it). If I had to choose between the two I'd give the edge to Clearwater as it has transportation to Tampa, better nearby restaurants, and has a little bit more going on (if you wanted seclusion you wouldn't really be going to either beach anyway).
Big fan of the specialty pizza's. Great pie, and would definitely recommend for anyone in the area. Wish we could have dined in and tried it fresh, but still had a decent crisp after we got it home.

The Gallery Pastry Bar is directly across from the Gainbridge Fieldhouse. The space is decently sized - cute and quaint. I really like the aesthetic and decor that is consistent in the entire bar. The bar itself looks very nice and there is a dessert counter on the opposite side of the room. 

We came here for an espresso martini and sweets. Both of which were very tasty. For some reason our martini came in a wine glass which made it feel like we were drinking a mudslide lol not sure if they normally use martini glasses. The desserts came from the glass case pictured. I ordered the lavender pillow cake purely to try something new. I can't quite put into words what it exactly is so you'll have to try for yourself. I have never had anything like it. I included a picture of the inside. 

Overall good experience. The breakfast looked very good so I will have to come back to try that.

Took my van here to get tires a few years ago. They told me about a test to see if it needed to be balanced.  I assumed they would come out and tell me it needed to be, knowing I would most likely pay for it.  I was shocked because he came out and told me I was all good and did not need to pay for an extra service.  

That experience sold me, because I was treated honestly.  The staff is friendly and they work fast.  Careful for old people in the waiting room who listen to the customer t.v. too loud...I recommend headphones lol.

Just would like to send a shout out to Tabetha at the Maplewood Licence Office. After being asked three or four questions that could have been show stoppers on my title request, Tabetha found a work around. Glad to get the job done in one trip.

We purchased our front loading washer and dryer about 4 years ago and purchased the extended warranty. I too have experienced many days waiting for someone to show up and had Sears tell me at least a couple of times that the appointment had been scheduled for another day, and I must have misunderstood.
Here's the latest. Over two months ago, the control board on my washer went out.
I was told that it would be delivered to my door on November 30. 
It never came. When I called to unload on them, dropping more F bombs than a person should, the exasperated girl on the other line informed me that they had a policy that I could get reimbursed for the money I've spent at launder mats.
She gave me the number and I filed a claim. They told me that they did not know when they would be receiving the control panel for my washer... they didn't anticipate it any time soon.
I decided to hire an independent contractor and just get the job done.
He researched the part, and found that the part was made by whirlpool and was on backorder until 2020. That's correct- 6 years from now.
We've gotten nothing but dishonest, sub par dealings from these idiots.
This is NOT the Sears I grew up with.
My question is this.... IS THIS LEGAL? I have never in my life dealt with a business run like this! 
At this point, I'm ready to chunk everything I've bought from them onto the sidewalk near the front entrance of the store.
If anyone wants to go in on a class action lawsuit, I'm in.
Poke nachos are the best. Unfortunate they were out of tuna. The restaurant manager came to apologized and offered to pay for our drinks. The pretzels are sooo good.

A group of 5 of us went for dinner and the service was just awful.  It took four requests by us to get water.  Our dishes came out at wildly different times.  There was a 30 minute wait from the time entree number one came out until the last entree came out.  The guest who ordered sushi and miso finally got his rice at the end of his meal.  The green tea had been steeping for so long that it was not drinkable.  It's too bad because this has been one of our favorite places.
Great service by Lori. 23 in our group and Lori did amazing job.  Food was excellent.  Oh my goodness lobster bisque was delicious.

I had the breakfast relleno, and it was great, although it could have used a little more salsa. The eggs were cooked like they should be, not to dry or runny. The serving size was plenty, as there was 2 poblanos on the plate. Overall my breakfast was very good.

The menu choices seemed to be unique I haven't seen too many breakfast/lunch places with duck confit hash on the menu. The drink choices seemed to be pretty varied, with many options for tea drinkers (I noticed herbal, black and green).

Service was great, our server was prompt and got our drinks right away, she checked several times for drink refills and to see if our food was up to par.

They've made a fan out of me.....for now. I hope they dont screw it up in the future.

My husband and I had been wanting to try this place since it's so close to where we live. We had some queso fundido, tacos, and nieve frita for dessert. The food had good flavor and the lady attending us was very sweet. I'm giving it 3 stars because we did feel like the service took longer than expected for it being a slow Sunday night. We were there for about an hour and a half, and when we finally got our bill we were told that they are cash only, so I had to rush to the bank to grab cash. We spent $50 for two people, which is why we expected a better experience. I'm cutting them some slack because they're a new establishment, I hope to return in a year or two to see if they improve.

I purposely didn't aim to expect much--after all its location in Vietnamese-starved Brandon and housed in an obviously former Pizza Hut building didn't bode too well.

GOOD ENOUGH PHO YA
Although pretty to look at (Contained all the typical ingredients with bright, crisp Veggies) my Meat Combo Pho was lacking... something. I don't want my Pho fake-ly flavorful but it definitely seemed like something was missing. But it was definitely not horrible and the nice warmth from the broth comforted me. Other dishes such as the Pork slices in the Noodle Bowl were also crisp with the fresh ingredients. Delicious and filling.

OKAY ENOUGH SERVICE
Over the course of our meal several different workers approached us in addition to our server. Although it was always helpful and a rather muted smile, the timing was always off. The menu could also be simplified a bit to focus more on what their best sellers are instead of trying to appeal to everybody--because it's doing the opposite.

Sorry. Where have you been my entire life Capriottis!? This place is so great! First, it's really pretty inside. This of course isn't a deal buster but doesn't hurt. The sandwich options are plentiful and the service is fun. My chicken cheesesteak was really good and will have me coming back for sure. Note that the servings are huge. Come hungry.

Had a great late lunch at OB. I love that they have two sides to this restaurant; one being a bar and the other just a nice size dining area. I love being able to dress up and go to dinner but also a casual atmosphere. Oak Barrel provides this experience and the full menu is available on either side. 

Started out with their charcuterie plate which had some nice options. Salami and salmon, several cheese choices, taster salad-dressing was tasty, fruit and toast. 

I loved my Mac & cheese and soup. So much bacon in the M&C. No complaints at all as you get bacon in every bite! My husband had a burger and it was cooked a perfect medium. I wanted his burger in all honesty. Fries were also good. 

Kudos to our server who made nice suggestions and kept our drinks full.

Over-rated. Much more creative pizza at Bazbeaux's and at Jockamo's. Tried it twice and can't say it's better than Dominos. Last nught's clincher was being given a wine specials list by the host. We chose a bottle before the server got to the table. The sever announces that all of the special wines are out except for one. (Not the one we wanted.)  DUMB. Quit handing out the list if it's mostly exhausted.

I came here for restaurant week. We had a reservation and still waited for about 45 minutes while the hostess gave us attitude for being antsy. Our server was also not very friendly. We got the calamari appetizer to share which was very bland and not crisp. The foie gras ravioli was very delicious but a very small portion and the NJ sea scallops with cauliflower fritter which was also delicious. Overall I had to give them a two stars even though their food would deserve a three/four star because of how terrible the service was.

Drove all the way here from New York just for their Bo Bun Hue. Compared to all the places I've tried in New York. Bo Bun Hue from this place is the BEST! 
Their Banh Cuon is very yummy also. You can taste the filling inside, and it's not dry.

Definitely will be back for their Bun Bo Hue!

You know what I'm not a fan. I think this please is a rib bit (haha) on the expensive side. The food is good. I loooooove their cornbread muffin but not for one of them and ribs for almost $20. The waitress was nice and we even chatted with some couples next to us. I just don't think the ribs were worth it. However I am use to grilling my own.

Can someone please give the host/hostesses a script for when customers enter the building? Rather than staring blankly for 30 seconds then demanding, "I need to see your vaccination card," or worse, just staring, saying nothing, and then demanding the card at your table, I suggest something along the lines of "Welcome to Campbell's. May I see your vaccination card?" without the mouth-breathing and in a friendly tone?

Have I not reviewed here? Because it's good heaven. The soup dumplings are addicting - worth an hour drive for us....several times a week! If I lived in the city I would eat here every day. Everything is delicious! If you want full dim sum, you have to go across the street to Ocean Harbor for the steam cart experience, but there are so many good things here it's a tough decision. Soup dumplings, pork with sauce noodle, Shanghai wonton soup, any of the traditional Shanghai dishes, you can't go wrong. SIX stars!!

If you've been to one Wawa then you've practically been to all of them. The experience is the same across the board. They have plenty of touch screens that you place your food or drink orders at that are relatively easy to navigate. 

You can order anything from fruit smoothies to their infamous hoagies. Every now and then they have what's called hoagiefest, where any hoagie is $4.99! They have a variety of menu items to choose from so just navigate the screens and you should be able to find something to your liking. 

They often have really good chocolate chip cookies near the register that are only 0.99. Here's a good tip though that I don't think many ppl know. You can sometimes order warm chocolate chip cookies from the touch screen for the same price! Who doesn't love nice, big, warm chocolate chip cookie from time to time? Treat yo self! 

I think the only negative thing that can happen is if you happen to order in the later hours after dinner, the staff preparing the food can take just a little longer to make your order because they are preoccupied doing other things in the station.

Really enjoyed the pizza here. As the other review said, it's similar to other build your own pizza places. I came in for lunch on opening day and had a pepperoni w roasted garlic. It is hands down the best thin crust pepperoni pizza I've had. They really piled on the pepperoni which is very important. I enjoyed the pizza so much I took my wife back for dinner that night. We ordered the Woody which is a ranch sauce based pizza w chicken, artichokes, and bacon. That was also very good. This will be my go to pizza joint in North Valley.

Decent burgers. Fries and TOTs were a 4-5 star side. The 3 star review is for two things 1) Overpriced - $23 for 2 lunches (burger, side and a drink) 2) From the time we got in line to the time our meal was in front of us ready to eat it was 20 minutes. For us it wasn't a huge issue but I imagine many people need that to be less for a week day lunch.

Just started eating here more regularly. The 3-6 sliders are a really good deal and tasty. My husband likes the long sahm silver and I am a fan of the pork tenderloin. Service is usually nice and fast. Beer is pricy but really where is it not these days?
Great food, beer and wine selection is awesome. And there is a cute lil market with tons of unique gift ideas where you can browse/shop before or after your meal.

Perfect for a cute little morning date with someone. Cute, neat, welcoming atmosphere that makes you happy you're awake this morning.

Their portions are a bit small, so not a place for a hearty brunch if you're starving -- their shakshouka is probably the largest volume and the most filling thing, and sausage shakshouka is pretty yummy! 

Steak and eggs is not too impressive, steak-wise, according to my boyfriend. 

I've also tried their Norwegian Lox Special -- the capers mix super well with the other flavors on the plate and it's a treat to eat.

Good location/venue, and an outside patio area.

Great margaritas (could use slightly more fruit added). 

Delicious tortilla chips and salsa, and ceviche served with a leaf of romaine lettuce and avocado along with saltine crackers? (not sure about the saltine crackers  ...was ok with the crackers, but was better with their tortilla chips).

Good wings, lettuce cups, tacos, and desserts, and the prickly pear utilized in some of the menu items adds local flavor.

Service was courteous, friendly and prompt. Atmosphere is casual and the restaurant kid friendly, though primarily an adult venue.

I frequent Blvd and love it every time. The staff is always friendly and the food is always delicious. I look forward to the seasonal changes on the menu because it's always a new interesting flavor. Great neighborhood spot.

This place reminds me of Lamill at home. I love it. 

The staff are really helpful, friendly, and patient people, and really they just want you to have an excellent coffee.  Last time I went I had a cappuccino.  It was excellent. 
 
Meanwhile, get the biscuit. It is literally the best biscuit I've ever had.  Have it with their sausage and jam. I want to say that everything is house-made. 

It is possible that your order will take a bit longer than you expect to get to you.  Try and be zen about it. It takes lots of work to made a quality drink, and those guys get super busy.  Hang out and enjoy the beautiful space.  If Evan is there, chat with him! That guy rules. 

I want to go to there. Right now.

This place by far has the best tacos in downtown Indy. I make a trip here at least once a week. The week I found it I came back 4 bringing someone different every time. They all love it as well. The staff is super friendly and will be more then happy to explain how it all works. I definitely recommend chips and salsa. You gotta ask them for it but so worth it! $5 house margaritas on Wednesday's too!

Great Idea but the portions for a $8.00 breakfast sandwich are really small and unsatisfying.
I had an egg. kale and avocado sandwich and it was pretty flavorless. 
They need to tweak this menu if they are going to survive in this market

Enzo's is stepping up their game ‼ they are serving quality pizza as always. I'm a huge fan of their cheesesteak  very hard to find a good place within the bucks area with good ones  but their cheese steak is fantastic. their chkn parm dinner is so good I'd say it feeds 2 people... for the price it's rite

Had an eyebrow wax and a pedicure done, they were very prompt in sitting me down in a chair and getting to work.

The pedicure was decent, and she did a nice job on my eyebrows.

I'm only giving 3 stars because they were very pushy for additional services.
A) telling me my fingernails (I work with my hands for living) need a manicure is understandable, but when I say no thanks please leave it at that.

B) Going on to me for 10 minutes about my facial hair (wanting me to do other waxes) left me very uncomfortable and not interested in having any further services done. Being in the middle of my pedicure at the time kept me seated.

I was looking for a nice restaurant for a special occasion - to celebrate someone's new job.  We arrived at Roy's a few minutes early, had a drink at the bar and then were seated at our exact reservation time. The table was covered with decorative trinkets and the inside cover of the menu had a "Congratulations on your new job, Lesley."  Needless to say, it was pretty special for her.  The food was delicious with some folks ordering the scallops and others the Ahi tuna.  The appetizer was the large canoe of a variety of items which was plenty for our party of 6.  Following dinner. the desserts were delivered (their special chocolate cake) and another plate was delivered to Lesley, a variety of sweets with a "congratulations" written in chocolate across the plate.  The meal ended with the group posing for a picture taken by our server and then the photo was quickly delivered to Lesley in a frame for her to take home. I would definitely recommend Roy's for a special occasion, but also for some great food and service.

Food is delicious, but portions are too small and everything seems over priced. Cocktails are good but again, over priced. I would love to go here more but I can't justify the cost. It's just not THAT good. The patio is awesome and the treehouse is cool.

Crack fries.... need I say more? That's all I come here for. Crack fries with cheese and a nice beer. Delicious!

I've tried several items on the menu and have yet to be impressed, so I just stick with the fries, which are good enough to get my 4 star rating. 

As far as service, I usually have good waiters but on my last visit our waiter was a bit forgetful and not as helpful with helping us decide on a beer to choose. Also I wasn't aware that sampling a beer costs $1. Just make a note of that, they will only let you try two tho so choose wisely.

We stopped in and quickly picked up a meal and dessert. The drive through was fast and we were quickly on our way this time. The location where we live is impossible to get into and lines are down the street. Soon as we got to Nashville we had to pop in an give them a try.

So badly want this to be 5 stars because the people who gave me the Pedi and Gel Mani were so sweet, skilled and thorough. The foot, leg and hand massage was amazing and I thoroughly enjoyed the prep and scrub by the aestheticians. I got a fresh pedi and gel mani for a wedding the afternoon/evening following my mid morning Appt and when I removed my dress pumps at midnight I was surprised to see that the paint had not held after many hours drying and then sandal time. My mani is already discoloring. Thinking this is not anything wrong with the aestheticians who seem 100% skilled and excellent, but rather with the cheap product purchased by the salon. So I suggest the owner hold onto your awesome skilled staff, pay them well and purchase higher quality polish.
Good menu with tasty food options. Seems a bit pricey for what it is, and there are other places equally as good for less $$$.
Ordered a chicken bowl with rice and black beans. Received a white rice bowl, no chicken, no beans. I wish they wouldn't have accepted my order at all if they were out of food.

Great haircut...a bit of Europe and Kiev charm.

Not your local yocal barbershop.  Very professional and warm concurrently.

While the Hollister Cajun Kitchen is still my favorite in terms of entrees, the new Calle Real location is a refreshing relief for people willing to make the drive out there. I mean, where else are you going to get a good chicken fried steak out here?

My friends and I came for a Saturday brunch, and despite being told that the wait would be 30-35 minutes, we were seated within 10. Apparently, no one hangs out waiting for their name to be called. The diner is spacious inside, with much more room between tables than at any of their Santa Barbara locations. If you're coming with a large party or have a medical condition that requires more accessibility, this would be the best Cajun Kitchen to go to.

The menu is the same as the rest of the franchise, but the specials and sweet drinks at the coffee bar set it aside from the rest. Don't like your coffee black or basic cafe items? Try an ultra sweet caramel latte instead. The specials here when we were there included an andouille sausage benedict and a grilled turkey sandwich, which didn't sound particularly special. We went for Kitch classics instead: the tri tip benedict, two chicken fried steaks with cornbread, scrambled eggs, and home fries, and fried chicken and waffles.

The quality here is very consistent -- I like that they use drumsticks and wing pieces for the fried chicken, personally, because the dark meat is delicious. Everything came piping hot and revitalized even the sleepiest of our table that Saturday morning. And, because it's the wonderful diner it is, everything was diner priced -- we each made it out of there having spent less than $20, including tip.

Save yourself the pain and park across the street at the Sprouts/Orchard Supply & Hardware lot -- this parking lot is tiny!
Fantastic service and food, fairly authentic with a bit of compensated fusion. I eat here every time I'm in town.
Much needed in the area . Food is fresh to order , fresh ingredients hence the name.  Prices are reasonable.  We will be back

I've only been to Mai here; she will give you a great, affordable haircut. Super-fast, too, thanks to the super sharp razor-cutters she uses. It's almost more she's sculpting your hair as she's cutting it. Modest set-up, not fancy at all.

It had been a few years since I've visited the dentist and I was extremely nervous. I had seen the same dentist for 23 years and when he retired, I didn't really know where I should go. After putting it off for nearly 2 years, I decided to make an appointment (the fact that I KNOW I needed a rootcanal didn't help with my promptness!) with Dr. Sukoneck and Wilson. Immediately upon arriving, the receptionist (Reese) made me feel so welcomed and comfortable. The dental hygienist, MaryAnn, also very sweet, made me feel even more comfortable than I did before. She also used this amazing new tool on me which polishes off any stains on your teeth (coffee, wine, etc...) Next, I had to see Dr. Sukoneck. It was very obvious I was in dire need of a rootcanal, which ironically began KILLING me the night prior to my appointment. Dr. Sukoneck had plans to leave the office early and when he heard how much pain I was in, put off his plans to leave early and immediately began to drill out the painful root (Step 1 of a rootcanal) so I wouldn't be in so much pain. I would recommend this dentist to anyone. They are so great.One thing I really appreciated about this office was that with each mention of bad news, they follow it up with some good news. For example, although I had neglected the fact I needed a rootcanal for some time, they made me aware that I had been taking really good care of my teeth overall and there was hardly any plaque buildup. It may not seem like  a big deal, but for how nervous I was, it really helped to put me at ease. I actually wish there were more than 5 stars, because this office deserves more than just 5. They will work with you on payments, they are not eager for the money like other offices I have visited, they honestly just want people to be free of any tooth discomfort and happy with their smiles. I think that's so wonderful and if you've been putting off the dentist for any reason, make an appointment here and I promise you will not be sorry that you did. A+++++

I love supporting this local business!! Fresh, super crispy and always delicious Korean fried chicken and consistently great service :) I personally like the honey soy and the chili sauces for the wings. Try their bowls as well! I have tried both the bulgogi and the spicy pork ones and they're mixed with rice, dumplings, japchae (noodles) and a salsa. The flavors are delicious and well balanced.

On 9/01/20 I got referred to Westside auto repair from a business who was shutting down because of COVID. Wanting to give business to my local peeps I decided to try this one out. The moment I got out I was not disappointed! I was met by a honest, easy to talk to man named Ivan. He was beyond nice, helpful, and quick. I got a diagnostic done on my vehicle he fixed what was needed or could around my budget which was less than I thought. I can't say enough how impressed I was of this lil auto place. But walking up you could tell that their work was above n beyond. I was not disappointed. The prices were more than fair n the service was remarkable! Definitely going back!

Weakest/worst $6 cold brew I have ever had. I can't speak for the smoothies but I would not order a coffee. This review is shorter than most so I have to keep writing in order to tell you that I will never go back here.

The food was excellent. Prepared EXACTLY as ordered and delivered promptly. Drinks were always refilled.
Restaurant was very clean.
A special THANK YOU to Ms. Leah who was my server. She was especially friendly, prompt, and professional. The ideal waitress.

Worst moving exeprience ever!. Let me start by saying that I did not hire these people directly. I hired Apt Moving which then turned out to just be a broker who stop talking yo me as soon as I payed the non-refundable $800+ deposit. These people broke all my glasses, lost a nightstand and a bench, and almost left with my $400 vacuum. They were about 7 days late and I was basically forced to pay another $500 just to get my stuff  expedited (after was already late). Ive been trying to contact them since the move to get refunded for the stuff they lost...no answer. The phone now appears to be disconnected. Do yourself a favor...pay a little extra for a better company.

I normally don't order hamburgers, but tried them when the previous owners were there.  I loved them and frequently stopped there!  When the new owners took over, I stopped by with my brother and sister (both from out of town).  I didn't like their hamburgers.  I don't know what they added to the meat, but I didn't like it at all.  The previous owners had very good, fresh food.  I didn't always get hamburgers!  I don't know if I will go back to the "new" place.  It's hard for me to return to a place, after being so disappointed.

OMG... Can I give this place 6 stars? Please? Hey Yelp!!! Listen! I need a sixth star.. ok fine... 5 stars it is.


Wow. Ok so, It's not because a restaurant is expensive that it's good. It's also not because everyone says a restaurant is good that it's good. This place. Is good. No, it's awesome.

Tucked away in the garden district, the Commander's Place is an example of what fine dining should be. Refined yet quirky. My fiancée and I came here to celebrate her 30th birthday 4 months after the fact with a dinner in style.

First impressions,
Exterior. I would have never guessed that this was the famed commander's palace. It looked more like something I would expect to see on the Santa Monica Pier or Coney Island, but once inside, I was instantly immersed into a realm that reminded me of a Ladurée in Paris meets the Blue Bayou.  Beautifully decorated we were greeted at the entrance with a man and a woman who received our reservations and showed us to our table. We were asked if there was an occasion for being here, we answered.
Soon after being seated our back up waitress came by and asked my fiancée if she cared to celebrate with some balloons. "Balloons?" she expressed, "Balloons!" was the reply! "Yes!" was the answer, 3 Balloons to our table did fly!  We were given the wine list with an explanation as to how to navigate through it.

Our Head waiter came to our table and instantly recognized our accents. 
-"Southern California?"  
-"How did you know?"
-"Call it a hunch, I'm from up North"
-"Ah"
-**Nods**

I think he sensed that my fiancée was nervous in this place, and not really knowing how to act, so he was trying to break the ice and make us ALL feel at ease. 

We ordered... wow. we ordered a delicious I think 8 course meal with wine pairings. No Regrets

But there was a problem. We didn't have the famed Turtle soup on our menu!!! So we asked if we could have a taste. Our waiter with a smile and a raised eyebrow, said "I'll see what I can do to get y'all a taste" (yes one quickly falls into the "y'all" thing here, everyone says it and it's so natural!) "I think we should bring it out as your first course, Yes... I think that will fit in just right"

Next thing you know we were blissfully escorted to a realm where our mouths couldn't get enough of anything. EVERYTHING was delicious! And the wine flights! wow no kidding! Descriptions of what was from where and what to look out for in the flavors made this a culinary experience. I frankly won't do anything any justice by explaining the foods to you, you'll have to discover those yourselves. Suffice it to say however we were STUFFED and happy.... And a bit tipsy.

And despite the fact that we were the last diners in the place our servers did not skimp a touch on the service, indicating to us that we were not to rush and that it's their pleasure to have us. (our reservation was a little late and the place closes relatively early, so do watch out for that!!!)

Ultimately when we got our bill we noticed that we weren't even charged for the turtle soup. When I indicated this to the waiter, he said:
-"You're our guest, we're glad you enjoyed it!"

We were offered a taxi to take our smiling faces back to our hotel!


Thank you Commander's Palace for a truly memorable evening!

I don't review places often, and for me to do so I have to be really impressed by something. My father in law lives around the corner from 1010, and we got take out from there tonight which we hadn't before with FIL. I have a lot of food restrictions so eating out at new places, especially pizza, can be difficult. I ordered a salad and asked for it to be made without croutons, onions, and olives and added tuna to it. 

I was so impressed at how every detail was done as I asked, at the portion of mine, my spouses and their dads, and how good it all was. The amount of tuna I got was enough to last me a few days. I'm also really picky with French fries and theirs were made to perfection and the portion once again was incredible. I'm so happy we finally went over and tried this place. 10/10 would go again and definitely will.

Having gone to Berthas over the years I know the food is good.   I went last Sunday, place was slow, it was near lunch.  Sit down and had the worst waiter ever.  This guy was a total jerk.  We were siting for 30 seconds when he came by  to take our order .  We asked for more time.  3 or 4 minutes later he's back, now we still are looking at the menu.  First thing I notice was the prices have soared up.  I mean high end prices for mexican food.   He again wants to take our order, I ask him if  they have carne asada and he says , no , very rude . I point to a dinner with steak and ask him if it's close to carne asada  and he says, Rude again...No , it's nothing like it .  So I order and I'm looking for something for my daughter and he waves his hand not me like when you want someone  to hurry and says ...What else...what else.   I look at my daughter and say , do you want to leave and she says ,yes.  I ask for the manager he says he's the manager .  As I walk out the door I tell the cashier your manager is a jerk is the owner here.  She points to a guy next to her.  I look at him and tell him what my  waiter did .  He shrugs his shoulders and laughs...he laughs.  I walk out and will never be back again.  Go to Miguls better food and much better prices .  Owners always there and nice.

Really nice and quaint place to enjoy cervice! I didn't get a chance to write my review right away and I apologize in advance for not remembering the names of the dishes and cocktail that I enjoyed! 
Oh, the desert was delicious too! Definitely worth a visit to try this place!

I've eaten at the Brewery in the past and had good meals, but after last visit I will never eat there again. My husband and I ordered an appetizer and entrees. We had the chicken strips app, lobster cakes and a steak. Nothing was seasoned! The chicken strips tasted like nothing, I don't even think salt and pepper was used. The lobster cakes were supposed to be a lump cake but there was so much filler in them and they tasted like nothing. The entrees came with risotto which was hard and gluey again with no taste. Literally like you were eating paste. The steak was well cooked but again no flavor. The waitress must have known how bad the food was because as soon as our dishes were served she walked over and asked how everything was before we could even try it and then disappeared. 

We never had a chance to even tell her about the awful meal until the very end because she was no where to be found. She was apologetic and said that they have been having a lot of complaints lately because of a new chef. She offered to get us another dish but we turned down her offer because after 3 failed dishes we just wanted to leave. I left hungry but went across the street and had a slice of pizza.

While I buy much online.  Audio requires some
Hands on research in most cases.   I frequent guitar center and have always had a great experience.   I have also purchased used gear here for a fraction of the cost.  I have had great experience with their warranty services as well. All around 5 stars

We have been here numerous times and loved it. Today we had the worst meal I have ever been served. Sirloin 1st try was black burned out side and raw inside, we wanted mediuim. Fries were fine. Sent back. 2nd attempt steak was better, but not rested. The fries were from the bottom of the basket with fish batter, brown burnt fries. Yes we complained and yes they too it off the bill but not sure we will come.back.

The shop is clean, and well lit. You're greeted right away! Prices are decent, and they offer a variety of services! I get my eyebrows threaded here, they've always done an exceptional job. I will never go back to wax! =) xx

I never had soup dumplings before going here and now, I always take people here when they visit me. Quick service so don't let a line by the door scare you. Portions are also big and I always take it home.

Great service at the bar but the food was way to salty; however since we ordered take out to bring back to our hotel at 12am, and we had been drinking for some time, it did the trick! We had the shrimp pasta-we asked for a side of the rice and beans but they just gave us rice (no beans anywhere lol)-and a side of French fries (those were very good). Like I said, staff from the front door to bartenders were super nice. They even gave us water in cups to take w us! 
Seems like this place might be new I'm sure they will work out the kinks!

Loved the service and the food was so delicious we came back the next evening for dinner.  The hummus and homemade pita was to die for.  My Greek salad was huge and filled with large chunks of feta and kalamata olives.  My daughter and husband enjoyed their meals too, grilled fish and a gyro.  We also tried their falafel.

Not my type of food since I don't care for fried stuff or eggy stuff.  But what I ate there was really good.  Especially some chicken soup that was best I had for awhile.  

Really liked the ambiance and the wait staff who were pretty and friendly.

Tried for the first time in January 2017 and have been back multiple times since. Authentic homestyle Mexican food. I had albondigas soup and the guys had posole (usually a weekend special) that didn't skimp on the pork. Entrée bowls for $7! Plus limes, shredded cabbage, cilantro and pico to add. Lots of happy oh-my-god-this-is-so-good slurping. If you have special request, be very clear - like no queso - or be sure to ask if you don't see exactly what you want - like chili verde tacos - on the menu. Sometimes your stomach's desire just happens to be available!
This Chinese place is very yummy! Their chicken is the best! It's really soft and juicy! Their rice and egg rolls taste good too. Strongly recommend this place!
This is one of our family's favorite places. The food is ALWAYS consistent (even during Oktoberfest) and the staff is always helpful and knowledgable! Great Food Awesome Beer & grocery selection!!

It's fall, the air is crisp, and you're itching for a change to bring in the new season.  What better way to change up your look than with a new hair cut or color?  I had this very urge this past weekend, so per the recommendation of two friends with great hair and rave reviews of Lakshmi, I booked a cut + color appointment with Kyle.  

I had an idea of what I wanted as far as highlights went, but I wasn't exactly sure how to articulate it.  I showed Kyle a few pictures and after a brief chat about my color history and confirming my "vision", she was off to mix up my color!

I really appreciated her attention to detail and the amount of time she spent checking my color to make sure it was the perfect shade.  She also gave me a great trim and a head full of waves to send me on my way.  I am so happy with the results and have gotten many compliments!

Everyone else at the salon was also very accommodating and friendly.  I was regularly being offered water, magazines, etc.  Lakshmi may seem pricey, but the level of professionalism, experience, and customer service make it worth every penny.  I will most definitely return when I'm in need of another cut or get the itch for a color change.

What a surprise! Very good coffee shop with a quaint comfy environment and even historic building! (Its an Old Railroad Depot!) 

Hey if you're in the 618 (Belleville IL) def give them a try!
Lamb, texture of beef jerky, overcooked and hard, then eggplant, same. Expensive food, inside has hip decor. Definitely in business for the name cuz it's not for the nom noms. Oh well

Every time I pass this place I think about my dining experience 8 months ago. It was essentially Persian food adapted for Main Line tastes...a disappointment if you've been exposed to authentic Mediterranean cuisine.
I really enjoy eating their wings especially the bbq ones. Great place if you want fast food chicken and a drive thru.

Simple.  No frills.  Great tasting.  Affordable.  All of this comes to mind when I think of Pizza Delicious.

The Garlic Knots (Ask for all the way) are downright illegal.  The pepperoni roll... Don't even ask for a bite.

Make your stomach happy and head to Pizza Delicious.

I have eaten here for years. The fish is very fresh, and we continued to enjoy our meals here. It has been a while, but my husband and I were looking forward to dining here again. First, the Oysters Rockefeller were tasty, but not hot. I ordered the sea scallops. They were just okay. Served swimming in water and butter, no seasoning to mention, but well wet and squishy. The vegetables were scarce and not impressive (they used to be awesome). The wild rice was salty, like rice a roni. My husband loves softshell crabs, and that is what he ordered. They were incrusted and deep fried. Too fried, too much coating. We both were so disappointed. It is expensive to eat here, and we expected more. I hope that management will read this and learn from their sister restaurant in Bethany. We eat at DiFebo's frequently. It is fresh, beautifully seasoned. The staff are professional. The Wilmington location lacks the atmosphere, it feels like a diner. The Bethany location is lovely. It is difficult to imagine they are owned by the same owner. I will not be back soon, but hope they shake it up, make it more inviting and have the chef pay better attention to the details.

Quaint and cute with all of the wine your heart desires!  You can get a glass or even try the flights. Gavin gives great recommendations! 

This is a great place to meet some friends after work for wine and laughs! They have a great wine selection and offer Two Tuesday's (2 glasses for the price of one). They offer small plates and coffee if you're interested. 

The decor could be a little more inviting. It's not really decorated, just tables and wine along the walls. 

I'll be back though!  We like it here!

Horrible experience here on a Monday night 3/26/2018.  There was a group 9 of us having a happy hour.  We were all getting out of work/arriving at different times.  Getting the attention of our server was like pulling teeth until we grabbed a chair at the bar at which time she was there in 2 seconds flat to tell us we were not allowed to do that.  when we tried to Order food like 3 separate times she told us she would not/could not take our order until the whole party was there.  However she was able to bring guacamole and chips and salsa no problem.  Then when we were ready to leave the server brought the check over to the table said I cant split this since you all arrived at separate times....This is really confusing because she couldn't take our order unless we were all there, but cant split the check because we came in at different times?  Not only does this not make sense, I cant imagine this is a common business practice of a restaurant that serves a ton of college kids.

I live out of town and wanted to take one of my oldest friends out for a special birthday. She recommended Katie's Pizza and Pasta, because it is a convenient location and it had an extensive menu. I had asked for a good seat and something special for our birthday celebration. Our waitress, Chelsea brought a mini bottle of Prosecco to the table as we were seated and the hostess honored my request from Open Table, seating us near the windows. My friend said the patio seating is wonderful in good weather and that they give young children pizza dough to play with to occupy them before the food arrives.

We were given complimentary Italian white bean dip with warm pizza dough like pita. It was excellent and flavorful. We ordered an appetizer, pizza, pasta and shared: the fried artichoke appetizer, the arugula dyed long spiral pasta with cream sauce and mushrooms and the pear pizza. Every item was unique, had distinct flavors, was fresh and delicious. The pear pizza was a light contrast to the rich but not heavy pizza. The mushrooms were sautéed in a truffle oil and were something I'd try to recreate. 

You can see them making the fresh pasta and it's amazing. I loved the lightness of the flash fried artichoke with the creamy dipping sauce and balsamic glaze. The pizza was almost like a savory galette tart. There were flavors of honey and some nice salty contrast of the prosciutto. It was beautifully made. Usually I'm a strictly red pizza devotee, but the pear pizza was unique and definitely a pizza I'd order again. 

The prices, including two generous pours of glasses of wine, were really reasonable for the quality and service. I live in the DC area where this meal would be twice the price. The salads and appetizers are higher for St. Louis, but not stifling. 
My friend said they have a great happy hour (3-6) and are a good place to have a nice meal with your kids. 

Our waitress, Chelsea was funny and attentive, engaging but not overbearing. She checked in on us but also allowed us to enjoy our conversation and meal. I also found out that they donate a day's worth of sales to a local charity each month. I love that concept and community engagement. It's a business whose values Is want to support. Would definitely recommend and come back to again!

I loved Raw! The selection and quality of sushi was great, along with the decor and overall ambiance. The price was very reasonable too in relation to the size of proportions. Definitely plan on going back next time in Philly!
Wonderful place in CBD. The food is very good and the prices aren't that bad. Loads of butter and flavor. Nice drinks. The chocolate chip cookies with beaters full of dough......crazy good!!!

Tucked away one floor beneath Weber Grill and TJ Maxx, Indy claimes fame to the "world's foremost interactive percussion museum". Part Disney attraction part musical oasis, the museum offers something for musicians and non-musicians alike. 

Highlights: 
-Drums from around the world and of different eras - my favorite was the drum made with human skin (not in a sick wth kind of way but in a wow! never would have thought to use human skin for an instrument way) 
-enormous windchime - possibly 9 - 10 feet tall
-Disney-like feel (after I commented on this to our tour guide I was informed the designer of the museum has also done some work with Disney - makes sense)
-highly interactive - opportunities abound to try your hand at various instruments

Notes for reference:
-The Center can be used for meetings and gatherings
-neat programming opps like drumming circle and make your own drum classes

**More of a street-level marketing presense needed. I was informed this is in progress. Great days are on the horizon for Rhythm! Discovery Center. I highly recommend a well overdue visit!

Good morning mouth!  I have eaten at First Watch in at least three states and it's always consistently good!  

On this visit I decided to try the BLT Eggs Benedict!  The flavor was great! Everything was fresh and perfect!  The presentation was arugula, arugula, arugula! Wild and Crazy arugula!  See the picture!  

Out waitress was super duper sweet and took awesome care of us!
Awful service.  Called to complain and the owner was very defensive and had an attitude.  They were not able to rectify the situation.

I can't believe the mediocre meal we just had at Devon.  The prices are 4 star restaurant, the food? Applebee's.  Tough fish and steak, and a 1.5 hour wait for our food. Embarrassed to host my family for a celebratory dinner at this huge let down.
The man behind the counter was grumpy and unfriendly.  The coffee was just OK, and mine ran out before my cup was full.  A new pot would have taken too long.  We will probably not go back.
Prices went up, but the size of the portions went down... Not happy at all and they've lost a regular!!! I haven't seen the original owners in a while so that may be the reason for all the change...
The rolls were good and service was fast. I was missing the dining experience of an authentic sushi restaurant. It was a pretty good experience for my first visit to Indianapolis.

Great sushi! I would certainly come back. My only issue is that I believe the servers should pay more attention to what their patrons order in its entirety instead of just the sushi. I love that they actually cook the sushi fresh and it's not buffet style. I would give them an A- only because they forgot one thing that we've ordered.
I had the "Thousand Dollar Chicken."  It was delicious. Would definitely order again. Our waitress was very attentive & did a great job. Would highly recommend to others.
Amazing!! We are here visiting from out of town and wanted a little cafe style lunch. Love the quaint home setting. The owner is so wonderful. Everything is so fresh, presentation is great.

Went in yesterday to look for a dry herb vaporizer, asked a few questions and after talking with an employee I got the snoop dogg g pro 2.0 by grenco science.  After having a few problems getting it to work, I contacted grenco science only to be told that what I purchased is not made by grenco as all the packaging says, it is indeed a counterfit.  Grenco doesn't make a snoop dogg g pro 2.0.  Be cautious of counterfit merchandise  in this store.

Absolutely terrible! I went there tonight with my girlfriend and she had the bbq chicken while I had the New York strip. I asked for medium rare with mashed potatoes and received well done with chunks of potatoes.  The bbq chicken was so over cooked it tasted like 2 day old turkey. We ordered the onion cheese bread and it came out dry(like 3 days old dry). Overall, everything we had sucked. This place is terrible and I don't know how they are still in business. Any low cost chain(such as chilis, Applebee's, etc) on a bad night is better then this place. Avoid this place at any cost

This is the real deal dim sum. Our group got there early Saturday so there was no wait. The carts were full of tasty items that we could not refuse - sticky rice, bean curd, shrimp dumplings etc etc. The sesame balls were the icing on the cake. 5 of us ate like there was no tomorrow and the bill was less than $15 per. It was just about 2 hours from the time we left the house in Suburbia to the time we returned. Obviously, authentic dim sum in Chinatown is not meant for long leisurely meals. High quality food, efficiently served - that's what this place offers.

My sister and I went to Caribou Cafe last night for dinner because she had received two gift certificates for free entrees there. We didn't know what to expect because of the mixed reviews we'd read, and after discussing what we would write about it on Yelp, I really hesitate to give this place more than two stars. 

Although the decor is quite nice and the wait staff seemed personable (our waitress was lovely), we were really disappointed in the quality of food and felt it was extremely overpriced for what it was. The wine list is decent, but again, too expensive for the quality. We started with the fennel, pear and almond soup which was actually quite good; unfortunately, the entrees were not. There are no vegetarian options at all (I knew this beforehand, but hey, free meal!), so I opted for the crab cakes. I really don't know how you can screw up crab cakes, but these were terrible. They were completely flavorless and I had to douse them with several lemon wedges to get any taste at all. The cakes weren't even properly breaded and were coated in this strange, thin, non-bread crust... it was odd. They were served with a very bland hollandaise sauce and some steamed spinach. I was very disappointed at the weak effort and high price ($27!) and have definitely made better ones at home for much less. Overall, a very boring dish. 

My sister ordered the special filet mignon, and was not thrilled about it. It was served with mashed potatoes and green beans. Although the steak was cooked perfectly and was very tender, she complained that the dish was very salty, and not worth the price. Again, we feel we could've had better if we'd made it at home. For dessert we split a creme brulee, which was decent, but nothing to scream about.  I really wouldn't recommend coming here unless you are heartset on overpaying for an uncreative, tasteless meal.

Lets say the food was great! Really!

Negatives: incredibly noisy and we were far from the bar
I brought a glass of wine to the table from the bar, i ordered a different glass she came to pour it not in a clean glass but in my used one, wine snob - maybe, but for this place the servers should be trained better. 
THE most annoying server, ever. She was CONSTANTLY trying to remove plates. We were clearly going to be her last table and she clearly wanted to be done. Even as we were engaged in a conversation in would come her arm. It was 10:00 on a Saturday night, the place was filled but no one else was coming in so WHY push it? 

The take away was not the great food but the annoying service. Clearly not trained in the art if fine dining.

First off, I will start by saying that the only reason I haven't switched to another office is because of Anne Salamone. She is the nurse practitioner that I see at this office. She has been very helpful the past few years and I never feel uncomfortable or that she's judging me when I am talking to her. My biggest issue is the wait time. I dread going for an appointment. I always wait at least 45 minutes in the waiting room, then I have to wait another half hour in the exam room before I am seen. This is absolutely ridiculous. I usually have to make my appointments for the evening because I am working during the day so when I go, I know that I'll most likely be spending my whole night at the doctors. Most of the staff is pretty professional and nice, I can't complain. I have had a few very negative experiences with very unprofessional young girls behind the desk. I vocalized my concern for one very negative experience I had because I was so upset and pissed off that this happened to me. I am most likely going to change offices, however. Despite that Anne has been great to me, I really am not overall satisfied with the office itself. They definitely overbook themselves.

Had a WONDERFUL dinner Friday evening at Amato's, great start to the weekend with a couple of bottles of wine at this great BYOB Italian rest. The sauce/gravy is just like traditional Italian style, I would buy it by the pint if they sold it! The eggplant parm is superb and the spinach artichoke dip was delicious...not heavied down with greasy cheese but made with fresh ricotta. The imported gelato was the perfect finish to dinner :) FINALLY a great Italian local rest.

My wife and I were driving and suddenly a rainbow of warning lights came on. A quick code check revealed a dreaded p0700 transmission issue. We took it into Tucson Subaru where they were able to diagnose the problem which was covered under an extended transmission warranty. Despite being busy leading up to the holiday they were able to get in, diagnose, and repair the problem within 24h! Everyone from reception to the mechanics were fantastic! I would highly recommend any Subaru owner to visit Tucson Subaru. Special thank you to service manager Jesse for making this process smooth. He called to check in w updates frequently and was able to get our car back before the weekend.

I love Yats! I thought I wrote a review for Yats before but maybe I haven't and that's hella shocking because Yats is life! 

Yats is creole comfort food that some may beg to differ depending on their taste buds but I love Yats. I will be in NOLA in July and I will compare but I am sure my buds will say Yats lol 

Whatever your vice is, Yats is the way to go. They used to give out IOU's for those that did not have cash and only cards which screamed loved for me. They now have CC machines so too bad those who were wishing on a possible eat here, play later idea. 

Yats has meals for both vegetarians and meatatarians. Their BB is the boss! It's black beans and corn, sweet and spicy. They also have many other vegetarian options. Their crawfish etouffee is life as well. Anything really is great here. Get extra bread to sop up the back tray pockets. 

Affordable, flavorful, you won't be disappointed!

This place has gone down the drain. We went there last night and service was terrible. The grills are electric and dont really cook that well. There is basically no ventilation. The servers basically bring the meat out and leave for extended periods if time. No buzz button. Their sign outside doesnt even light up. Such a sad restaurant.

I just rescued a 11 month old pit she needed to be spayed. I called my vet I go to they wanted double the price of this office.  And my other pup has health problems that are very costly on a monthly  basis.   The staff was kinda and the Dr was wonderful after. Told me about the surgery and after care needed.  My first experience was phenomenal.  My parents will be using them tomorrow.  I also got a bag with meds and instructions that also had her leash and harness and it and when I got home I found a little magnet with her picture in it that really made me feel like they cared.

Oh Sahm's place is amazing . We moved to the area last year and the previous homeowners left us a note with suggestions for places to eat . Sahm's was top of the list and they weren't wrong ! Good food, beer, and casual setting. Nice place to go hang out with friends and enjoy drinks and comfort food.

Sunday was my first time renting. This location is the only one I found open on a Sunday. They have after hours drop off and everyone was really nice! 

The car was clean and they were very quick and efficient. Will rent here again!

Their food is good, but I feel like their size has gone down.  They also didn't do what I asked them to do- take the veggies off of the sandwich.  The food tastes amazing, but I feel like their service is going down.

Before you write Mas Tacos off as a hipster paradise/fad, try them out. Guaranteed, you're in for a treat. My entire experience at MT (from walking up to the building, to ordering to eating outside) reminded me of Austin. I don't know if the owners are from there, but it's definitely the vibe I got. This isn't a bad thing. Rather than the most authentic Mexican food experience possible, I think Mas Tacos serves up some very yummy Mex-texish (my word) fare that's decidedly more 'blue dot and weird' than anything else the Lone Star state has to offer. Add in a healthy dollop of 'San Diego' for good measure.

Be warned: you will order more than you can eat. Everything sounds so good and is (relatively) fairly-priced, you're going to be tempted to order a ton. Take it from someone who ordered way too much: plan your order and then order one thing less. Your stomach will thank you. I started with the watermelon-lime agua fresca. Whatever you do, avail yourself of agua fresca. Whenever it's on a menu, I order it. MT's didn't disappoint. Packed with flavor but light and refreshing for a late summer day, I could have consumed gallons of the stuff. It's a good thing I didn't, because I ate way too much as it was.

I started with the chicken tortilla soup. Far from what you might remember from a popular fast(er) food chain (which, if I'm being honest, has decent soup for what it is), this is without-a-doubt homemade and magically delicious. You'll want to drink the broth. The soup is filled with tortilla, cheese, cilantro, tomato, corn, and shredded chicken. The avocado which topped by soup and filled the bowl was a welcome addition. I found the soup a touch lime-y but I like citrus. If your taste isn't accustomed to tartness, ask for a sample before diving in. For the main event, I ordered the fish tacos. Freaking awesome. HUGE pieces of tilapia, surrounded by onion, cabbage and dill. Perfect. My mistake came in ordering three of them. I was expecting the small, wimpy fish tacos you can get at other places. Not so here. These tacos are substantial. Order wisely. The only bummer of the meal came from the eating environment. Since the day was nice, we ate outside... and were swarmed by flies. They were everywhere. It made eating tough and not the least bit appetizing. Granted, it's getting colder now but in the future, I'll make sure my MT meals are conducted inside.
Luhv this place! Food is reasonably priced and is soo good! My non vegans friends even luhv it here! This is my favorite place to eat around here!

I checked out Bourbon & Branch for the first time last night, Friday night happy hour into evening. It was very busy but not unpleasantly packed.The cocktail menu is amazing. Their menu is pasted into pages of old children's books.The one I got was "What Is a Stranger and What Should I Do?" which was wonderfully creepy.  My bartender Kate was extremely friendly and knowledgeable.She started me with "The Hemingway" rum cocktail-it was sweet and refreshing. Because so many of the drinks sounded tantalizing on the menu I decided to switch it up to the "Branch Cosmo" for my next drink.It was such a refreshing change from the saccharine sweet that you have come to expect from your typical cosmo.Fresh cranberries and orange were muddled into the Tito's vodka.It was delicious.Both the Hemingway and the Cosmo were made with all fresh ingredients and were both balanced and stiff. They tasted the way a beautiful spring day feels.

There was a shift change and Brendon took over on bartending duties.I noticed it was still happy hour so I figured I would take advantage of the specials and order an Old Fashioned.It was easily the best Old Fashioned I had ever had in my life. I can definitely see myself going back to Bourbon & Branch for many many more of these.

The cocktail prices might have seemed a little expensive at first glance but they were all WELL worth the price.

By this time I realized I was pretty hungry so I decided to order some food.
