The Irish nachos appetizer was awesome and more than affordably priced.It was ample enough for 3-4 people to eat. Since it was just me,there were PLENTY of leftovers.

I can't wait to go back and try the rest of the menu there.I had a really tough time deciding which thing to get,especially after seeing so many other patrons' food go by that looked simply amazing.

I joined anytime fitness out of state and when I moved to the Boise area this location was the closest to my home. I like that you can access the club 24/7 but immediately began having problems when my key, and I that if other members I noticed, only worked about 30 percent of the time. I tried to talk to staff about it but they were never there even during the posted hours when they were supposed to be. I finally reached out to corporate after I had woke up at 6am on weekend and couldn't get in again (this was after I left a message at the gym and they never returned my call). I heard back from corporate and they said that the gym was banning me, accusing me of writing on the door in lipstick! This is ridiculous! Everyone who knows me knows I don't own a single tube of lipstick and have never worn makeup In my life! So because I issued a valid complaint against them they are trying to redeem themselves by making up false accusations! I have never been treated so poorly by a business in my life!

Charcuterie platter, Pates, terrines, boudin, pork belly sandwich, pig mac...

I've been taking visitors to Cochon for years and was thrilled when the butcher opened. The lines and get quite long around lunch time, so I've found that calling ahead for pick up helps get you out the door faster. Take the meal to nearby Lafayette square or across town to city park or Audubon. The charcuterie platter and all the meats make for a great picnic.

Worked here for a few years and all I can say is there are many options and if you are out and about or in the city for a day check it out, there is something for everyone, and if not step outside and go left or right and you will find something to
fill that craving!

Kit was able to accomodate me today on very short notice. Outstanding service from start to finish! He was very responsive via Yelp for scheduling and a quote. I was in by 10AM and the vehicle was back in my possession by 2PM. Photo is a 2018 Mazda 3 Machine Grey Metallic paint with 30% tint on 4 windows and rear glass. Do not hesitate to use Kit for your auto tinting needs!

I'm highly disappointed in this club. We were in the club last night oct 27 2018 for the freak show. Table service was great secretly service was great but...... a worker by the named of Jen was awful to me I mean awful iv never had anyone treat me that rude in my life. I was in tears!!! She was in my face and completely disrespectful. She ruined my time at this club. I would not recommend anyone to come nor will I be back.

This hotel met my expectations! I booked my stay according to TripAdvisor reviews. It was very modern, clean and I really enjoyed the music they played in the lobby and front entrance.
I booked this stay dependent on the location and breakfast. Gym would have been nice but it was only cardio and free weights (no machines or cables). The room was spacious, immaculate in cleanliness. I would have enjoyed a microwave, free bottled water ($3.50ea) and a bathtub so I could shave my legs easier, haha. The breakfast was varied day to day which I also liked. It would be nice if they could have left the coffee on for longer than breakfast time, otherwise excellent stay!

Went here recently during restaurant week for my girlfriend's birthday.  I was a little shocked how fast they shoved each course down your throat. We were finished entrees not even 40 minutes after we sat down. We didn't even go that early in the night so not sure why they were rushing. We were filled up so quickly we barely touched dessert and ended up taking half our entrees.   

The snow crab was great and my girlfriend loved her crab cakes but my steak was 100% burnt (ordered medium). I'm not one to send food back because I hate causing a scene so I didn't but I was recommended the steak so I ordered it and was very disappointed.  Waitress was very nice and helpful and lobster bisque was great too.  Just can't believe they would serve steak that well done to anyone at all. It was a waste of money. But hey can't win em all.  Moral of the story do not go here during restaurant week.
They are known for their sandwiches on soft pretzels . I tried the Turkey Pretzel Sandwich and it was Delicious

I ordered the Chicken and Steak hibachi and it was delicious. Very filling. It came with yummy dipping sauces with the hibachi. If you want to sit at hibachi tables on the weekend you must make reservations (which was a bummer for walk ins) The desserts were decent but not really worth getting. I will be back for sure!
Most amazing dinner I've ever had! Try everything and don't miss the Turkish hummus, the sable or the duck hearts!
had a redeye flight and took the shuttle at midnight to hotel.  reserved a king size bed and were too exhausted to ask to change room to one that had a king bed.  make sure you get what you reserve.

Delicious BBQ at a descent price. They also have a really nice draft lineup with yummy local brews. Try a Daredevil brewed just right down the street!

One thing I really love about BBQ & Bourbon is the family-friendly atmosphere. The owners are two of the nicest people you'll ever meet. It's places like this that are bringing Speedway back to life!

Went here twice during our vacation to Nashville. The first time we had a fantastic experience. We had the Thursday special- it was a Chorizo and Wagu burger topped with black bean queso and Fritos. It was delicious! Their special sauce is out of this world. I like the vibe and the beats  we came a second time last night. They forgot to put our order through so we waited 40 minutes for a burger. Service was not as attentive. Left pretty disappointed and felt like we shouldn't have come back a second time.

Beautiful decor. They did an all day Saturday happy hour. Great deal!! The red sangria was alright and a couple good options of cider.

I wouldn't necessarily recommend it for authentic English food, but it was decent. Only tried the scotch egg in fairness; however, it would have been loads better without their random sauce that overpowered the food.

Staff are friendly and manager was good in regards to my tables' professional English opinions. Hahah

 Will definitely come back to try again another day and hopefully increase my review rating.

Currently, they have an amazing New Years Eve special of 50% off everything with $10 bottles of bubbly.

I loved the food, but I hated the experience. Employee, Adrianna, gave us the worst customer service you could ever give a customer. Hated that. Won't be coming back to this location. If you want a good burger with great customer service go out and try burger republic! Best of Both Worlds!!

Got a wedding cake from Isgro's.  Beautiful and delicious!  Went for lemon swirl and chocolate chip with buttercream frosting.  Took extra slices of cake to go at the end of the night.  Made for an awesome breakfast!

What an amazing experience! I needed to have some extensive work done to repair a damaged door and roof on my vehicle and I am SO happy with how it turned out. Tracey and Erin are wonderful to work with and made everything so simple. Tracey got me my quote within 10 minutes and she made sure to point out some stuff on the estimate which might seem odd to someone inexperienced like myself and tell me WHY it was needed. My work was estimated to take 16 working days so I figured about 4 weeks since also dealing with insurance to get things going, spot on, they worked with my insurance company and assured me they would make sure to fight to get the job done the right way, not the cheap way the insurance companies prefer. My truck is very sentimental, it was my dads truck before he passed away six years ago so it is my baby and extremely important that the job gets done right and I felt very safe leaving it in their hands. The truck also has a specialty paint that sparkles beautifully in the sun, so I was glad to hear that they make their own custom paints there so that they can match up the size and density of the sparkle in my paint and they did a great job, it's an exact match, you can't even tell it's had any work done and to me that is exactly how it should be. Hopefully I won't ever need to have any body work done in the future but if I do this will be the only place I go and the only place I recommend.

It was already good. Really improving the quality and consistency by the month. I don't really go anywhere else in OV for Chinese anymore. It would be unfair to leave the rating where it was and like I said... I only go here now. I cannot wait for it to get to the five star level.

WORST EXPERIENCE for Breakfast Ever! 2 Sundays ago I was in need of some nourishment, now normally I would go to Lisa's a little down the street from this place but they were not open and they do not deliver, or if they do I don't recall. I ordered from the corner grill, 2 sausage egg and cheese sandwiches on kaiser with fried onions and Ketchup. They offered to make it a meal for $5, with hash browns and a orange juice and have it delivered. They called me back 4 times to ask what my order was... OK  they came 45 minutes later. the food was cold the meat was overcooked and of poor quality, they used old horrible bread and they onions were raw and they forgot the ketchup.... I don't know what happened to this place but when it was greens corner deli... pretty awesome. Still pretty good when the college kids owned it. NOW its the worst place for food, even worse than old McDonald's that was found under a childs car seat!.... Please don't ever go to this place, let them go out of business! YOU HAVE BEEN WARNED! Disgusting.... and I am usually an open minded and fair guy just don't want anybody to feel as sick as I did after that DISGUSTING and horrible experience!

I love this place! The food is always fresh and delicious. The Mediterranean style good is just so yummy I don't know how else to say it. Just darn right good. The owner/cook? Is really nice and always friendly and cheerful. They have a drive through and sit in to dine as well. 

One time, I stopped by late morning early afternoon for lunch and he asked me how I was and I said good and I asked him how he was and he responded and he added because I'm the first person to ask him how he is today, he gave me a free soda with my meal! How sweet. Left a great impression on me.

I love the Cup Cafe not just for their great food, but for the love they endlessly show to the community that they welcome. Patio is awesome when the weather is just right and inside is always very pleasant, even sitting at the bar to eat since we don't drink.

They really hung in there during the horrible pandemic and its their 100th year anniversary. 

Blessings to the Hotel Congress and all they serve here in Tucson.
We didn't get tickets but waited in line for 1 1/2 and scored two seats inside. Was worth the wait and really cool to see. Very small inside and they pack the house.

A true artist in a dying industry.

I had been looking for a stylish peacoat for literally 3 years to no avail.  The issue is my size (very tall and slim); it was impossible to find a coat that fit me well.  I ended up buying a XXL peacoat that I liked with the hopes of having it successfully tailored to end up being more like a XLT.  I took it to Armen and he took material out of the stomach area and extended the sleeves a full 2".  Now I have a perfect coat that I love.

I now feel that I no longer have to settle for clothing that doesn't fit well.  I would never consider taking my clothes anywhere else (ESPECIALLY dry cleaners ugh) for tailoring.

Previous veterinarian, Sabino Canyon veterinarian, couldn't seem to get a grasp on handling my cat. He's not a tiger, he's just a Siamese. But Dr. Upchurch handled him with ease and didn't even asked me to medicate him, as Sabino Canyon did. I was very impressed with her. Ironically after talking with friends, they all like their cats there. Great veterinarian. Highly suggest. Especially if you have cats and no dogs. Then you really need a vet that understands felines. Other vets seem to have more of a grasp on dogs. In my experience. Not sure if that's just because dogs used to be the number one household animals. But since then, we all know cats are in the lead.

I went to get a quote, and was greeted as soon as I walked in. What a great shop! The tattoo shops around here make you feel like you shouldn't be there. Not at Marcs. The manager, Cole is who I spoke with. She knows her shit, very informative, and an amazing artist. Her work wont disappoint! VERY CLEAN shop, awards, and original art everywhere. I wont ever go anywhere else! Thanks Cole, cant wait to come back! I've also never had a tattoo heal faster!
great envirnoment and great beer selection.

We were very happy with it. We are not farm-to-table people. We're those horrible people who frequent the fancy steakhouses where you can get an 84-ounce tomahawk ribeye! This is not that place. These are normal, human size portions of unique dishes, and it was delicious. Food was so tender (we had the steak, pork, and chicken). All very flavorful, and obviously fresh. Also had the chocolate and banana desserts. All excellent and we will be back. Thanks

Me and my wife went here for the first time and will be coming back. Service is excellent as our waitress was very knowledgeable and patience with us. The atmosphere is laid back as for the food which was reasonably priced and delicious.  The hookah flavors add a melon yet good chill vibe for this laid back experience. While it is a 21 and over hookah restaurant there is no heavy smoke aroma in the air.  I would definitely recommend anyone giving it a try if your up for a chill afternoon or a mello evening..

Great little tea lounge that mixes bubble tea with more traditional tea enthusiast.  Unfortunately, they close pretty early at 10PM, even on the weekends.  A good mix of students cramming for exams, friends have a chill night playing some board games and people typing away on their laptops.  Definitely a nice get away if you're a student at near by USF...

Rude staff.
I had some items I needed to return that I purchased from another store. I called them beforehand and asked if I can return them and they immediately responded, "Yes that would be no problem at all". I drive out there to find out they wouldn't accept my return because some of the items were still at the warehouse and it would be "too difficult to manage the inventory". They responded in a terse unprofessional manner. 
If you're forced to go to a Mens Wearhouse, I recommend looking for another one in the area.

Tried to work with these people on a rental. The showing was rushed, the emails were inconsistent and dealing with the continual run around makes sense now that I've read the other reviews. It seems they make a lot of excuses. I am grateful now that I dodged a bullet by not renting from them.
Food was good. I've had better but I did enjoy my meal. Didn't feel like it was cooked by an Italian. Service was amazing. I really enjoyed the family restaurant feel.

Reservations required during Covid. 

Wonderful zoo. Great set up / layout. Ample parking and a great location next to Saguaro National Park (west). Restaurants were mostly open and the facility was otherwise running at normal capacity. This place was clean, and had hand sanitizer dispensers throughout. I would estimate that 90% of everyone there were masked up and respecting others. It was our first time there and we would recommend!

One bummer was the Stingray "Touch" exhibit was open but no one was allowed to pet or feed the stingrays .

Showed up with a couple of minutes until they opened and they waved me off...uhm ok.

Went back a few hours later just to check out the selection of stuff people pawned when they had to have their gambling fix. Really kind of poor selection of stuff and they are pretty pricey on everything.

I'd pass based on service and prices.

I'm glad to see that Reno is finally getting some upscale spots- that dingy 1970's western feel is getting pretty tired. 

Aura is the Silver Legacy's newest addition- not a club, but a smaller "ultra lounge".  Its decorated pretty nicely, with a blue theme and lots of pretty lights.  They also offer bottle service, another new addition to Reno.  I'd be interested to see how this place is on a weekend.  Its nice to see a new upscale spot in this city filled with dirty, tired old bars that cater to 50+ gamblers.

I ordered the classic burger with fries, jalapeño poppers and topped it off with some bread pudding.  This was my first time here and won't be the last.  The atmosphere is very laid back. As I entered, Maxwell was playing in the background.  As soon as I approached the counter and gave my name...my food was ready and hot.  The only thing that I found wrong was the ranch sauce that was missing for my jalapeño poppers.  I definitely have to come back with my wife.

I was very disappointed with this particular restaurant because it's one my favorite restaurant chains. The manager (a female) was not attentive to us when 4 out 8 people at our table was served and 2 happened to be children. She heard our compliant and never returned to let us know what was going on or to even apologized or ask us how our food turned out. By the time the food came out, the other 4 people were almost finished and the kids had to eat bread because they were so hungry. I was never treated so poorly at any other cheesecake factory before in my life. When getting the check, the manager did take off the 2 kids entrees. but I had to let our waiter know that my dad and I didn't get our burgers until everyone else was done eating. How long does it take to cook a burger??????? Like really.

One positive thing, was the view. Hell, I'll take good service over view any day.

Valet was pretty pricey @ $22.00 a car. I would rather stick to Cherry hill, KOP, or Willow grove's cheesecake factory. I will NEVER visit this cheesecake factory location again.

My visit took place on 11-31-15

Just moved to East Nashville and this place is just out my back door.  Good service, good drinks and decent food.  The only recommendation I would have is that they trim down their menu a little and specialize in a couple of items instead of spreading so thin.  There is a lot to choose from on the menu but sometimes less is more in my opinion.  Overall a great place to go for dinner/brunch/lunch and hang with friends.

Of course you have to visit this place! It's home to the famous bananas foster. We had reservations at 9, but our table wasn't ready so we got drinks at the bar I got the Caribbean milk punch and hibiscus Pimms cup. The hostess got us to tell us that are table was ready.  The drinks were awesome. There is a self playing piano. The ambience was nice and the courtyard look great with a fountain. 
We had appetizers for dinner. I got the blue crab remoulade and New Orleans bbq lobster. They were delicious and light. I  didn't feel like eating a big meal b/c I wanted dessert and the famous bananas Foster was born here. You have to order two or more in order for them to make them. It's great to watch them make it table side. The dessert was awesome. The sauce was not heavy or sweet and not too much liqueur. The ice cream was light and bananas were good. It's a nice little show lol.

By far the worst McDonald's I've ever been to. My terrible experience typically is one or a combination of poor customer service; (1) the staff are incredibly incompetent &/or (2) the technology of McDonald's is functioning poorly or in need of repair. These two issues I would estimate are the main reason why the wait at the business seems to be in excess of 30 minutes and that's if you actually get served. It's sad when I have to go all the way to the Hampton location b/c although I know that one will be slow as well, at least I get served. Please don't spend money at this location. Let it fail as it deserves to. If there comes a time in the not-so-distant future where the Missouri legislature actually has a discussion about a state of minimum wage do not send the employees of this McDonald's because they will ruin all chances of a $15 minimum wage. If I could give negative stars I would.

This place was incredible! After I got out of class early, I decided To make the drive up to Tucson to see what it has to offer for food. Thanks to Yelp I was guided to this place.

Oh my lanta. The sweet potato fries. Perfection. Fried pickles? Oh don't get me started. Pretty sure I had the money burger which I had to dislocate my jaw to eat, but it was so juicy and delicious, my tastebuds were very excited.

They had beer!! That completed the meal. Burger and beer. A couple that always goes well together. I highly recommend this place If you want something different. I'd say the food is worth the price. :D

The Drury Beer Garden really is a hidden gem. It's a great place to just chill out with a larger group of friends without having to worry about squeezing everyone around a bar. The atmosphere is warm and friendly and I think because of this everyone freely intermingles with other groups. Just your regular backyard party coupled with an awesome beer list and the chance to meet some people. What is there not to like?

I went this past weekend and scored a picnic table under a heat lamp. I had my favorite beer: Hell or High Watermelon for $5 a can and couldn't have been more content!

found this on Yelp and and was impressed with David and his service, from an on time arrival, and a clean and better than expected jumper, also rented tables and chairs that were clean and in good working condition, and  priced very fairly.
I WILL definitely use this company again and WILL highly recommend to friends and family 
thank you again

Always have a great time here. Sometimes come here before enjoying a show at the Pioneer Theater, sometimes come to simply enjoy sitting by the river, enjoying their patio area and great fun to enjoy several of the Happy Hour specials. Their Happy Hour Menu starts at 4pm and you have many choices and it's fun sharing a few of these. Great place to sit on their patio and people watch while you enjoy and hear the river.
Dinner here is pricey but not when you consider the quality of the meals, the location and the ambiance. You could pay the same somewhere else and not have that same quality and ambiance. I do recommend. Anything you order here will not disappoint. Staff are extremely pleasant and helpful. Love your dog and love to take him/her out occasionally? Your doggie is welcome here on their patio!

I used to be a regular at Hesslers on Karaoke night.  A long time Patron of 10+ years.  That was until they switched DJ's.  The new DJ played regular music for about 30% of the night, which prevented those of us who wanted to sing from getting up more than once.  Unless of course you were a hot girl shaking your booty in the creepy DJ's face.  Those girls were able to get up multiple times.  

I was there from 9pm when Karaoke supposedly started (DJ didn't actually bring anyone on stage until about 9:45) until midnight and got to sing 1 time.  In the old days I would get to sing 3+ times.  For those of you who thought that DJ Rich was unfair, you are WAY off.   You shouldn't expect to show up at 11:30 and sing twice.  DJ Rich was fair because he kept a rotation.  I always knew when it was my turn because it was always after the last person I sang behind.  This new guy does NOT do it that way.

I miss the days of the regulars like Mr. Six Flags and really enjoyed the entertainment of some really decent singers.  All those regulars are gone now.  Nice Job Hesslers, send all of your normal patrons away.   I will no longer bring groups of people to experience my (used to be) favorite karaoke bar because I don't plan on going back unless they bring DJ Rich back. 

It is sad, because Hesslers obviously does not care as long as they are making money.   Shame on you Hesslers!

I wouldn't recommend this company if you need a new garage. The installation process has been a headache with many hiccups along the way and they still wanted to charge us full price. A good company with good customer service should refund the customer a portion of the cost and offer some discount when the company messes up. That was not offered to us and during the process I have had to wait while they fixed the mistakes on their end (ordering incorrect and defective parts). Still in the process of waiting to get our final product. This whole process has taken way too long. We should have gone with someone else.

First of all, staff was very rude and aggressive. They practically threw our meals on the table. They waited til after we opened our beer to tell us there was a 15 dollar automatic charge per person for alcohol. On top of that, after receiving the check, while we were hanging them our card they told us the restaurant was cash only. We had no cash on us and had to ask another table to pay for us. Extremely embarrassing. Never refilled our waters or came to check up on us. Waitress seemed very annoyed. Disappointed, expected more from this place.

We are visiting Tucson and planned to have a low key Christmas Day.  We used the pools where we are staying and then had a 90 min foot and body massage, incredible.  We were driving around looking for a restaurant that was open and almost giving up - going to Walgreens or CVS to buy junk food.  I googled restaurants open Christmas near me and Tamarind showed up, it was 1 min away.  It was a meant to be Christmas gift...the food was the best Indian food we have had, service was great, the restaurant clean and modern.  We are from Seattle and have lots of great Indian food, but the flavors at Tamarind were the best.  Try the black pepper chicken appetizer, it was awesome.  If we lived in Tucson we would be back - we highly recommend this restaurant!!

The cheesteak was good, but not up to my Philly expectations.  Jim's is better. Rasmus' bitch was nowhere to be seen and the guys behind the counter were friendly enough.  I also like the energy of the place within the Reading Market.  For desert, go for the nearby Apple Dumpings (with heavy cream) in the Amish corner.
I really enjoyed the food and drinks. So far the best of places as this was my first time. Most definitely will go again.

I have been to the Libertine several times and I am not the type to want to spend a lot of money on a drink.  The drink prices here are  a little bit high, but well worth every penny.  Some of the drinks are it or miss, but most are amazing.  The staff is friendly and I love the music they play.  the clientele is fun as well.  I had the bacon flight which is amazing.  The wings were not very good, however.

Just got here. Place looks fantastic so far.  Sat outside and they had plenty of fans to keep it comfortable. Smoked old fashioned was the highlight of the night in taste and uniqueness. Guacamole was great but the chips were a little not crispy, but still edible.  Both the old fashioned and the Guac were equally expensive at 10.25 for the Guac and 11 for the drink.  I wanted to try both and enjoyed them, but next time I may skip it and go for a beer instead.  My wife had the margarita and wasn't totally wow'd by it....and it wasn't served in a margarita glass, just a tall glass.

Our group of friends had a variety of just about the key things on the menu.  I had the Skirt steak, my wife had the fish tacos, others at our table had the chorizo burger and we finished everything off with a four way split of a cuban sandwich.

My skirt steak was OK, the beef came out cold in the middle, but I think it was because it may have sat while other orders were getting prepared.  Loved the mini carrots on the side and the beans and rice were also OK but needed a little more flavor.  

Cuban sandwich was on point (except it didn't have any salami...) and they used real cuban bread from La Sagunda in Tampa.  The ham was great and the pernil/pork was also very good.  All the key ingredients for a great pressed Cuban.   

Service was also very good however it did take a while to get our orders out.  I suspect this is because the restaurant has been open less than a week and they are probably still working the kinks out.

Outdoor seating was plentiful, indoor seating looked pretty limited to the bar and a few tables inside a small house-turned-restaurant, but don't be afraid to sit outside.  We were quite comfortable with the many fans they have scattered on the ceiling.  

Overall, we were pretty happy but not 4 and 5 star happy.  I'll give it a few more weeks to work out some kinks and maybe some menu adjustments and try it again.   It's worth the try for the cuban sandwich alone and sitting out in a pretty cool outdoor seating area!
Only here for aps and drinks, but yummie stuff.  Punch of the day was delicious, fried olives with mozzarella were over the top!! Fries and beans were good too. I would definately go back!
I don't know why it takes 30 minutes in a drive threw to get an ice tea. Terrible service.

The flavors of this place are great. I can't deny that one bit.

My only gripe is the portion sizes are painfully small. My pad thai was in a very small container and my immediate thought was, this is not worth the price.

Wife's green curry came int he same container, but when you consider that it comes with rice in a separate container, you realize that since rice is whats actually filling you up, that's fine.

The best vintage store in St. Louis, especially if you are looking for mid-century (50s/60s/70s) clothing or furniture. I found a really cute polyester dress here as well as a Danish modern coffee table in mint condition. They have tons of accessories (esp. purses), groovy lamps, and more. Things are well-organized and clean (although the basement is a bit dingy), and best of all, items are reasonably priced!! Incidentally, I thought this place was called Cherry Bomb - I guess it's Retro 101/Cherry Bomb - two great stores in one!

This meal has been the best food I've had since............ Possibly ever. The food was amazingly prepared, the staff was super friendly and attentive. Service was perfect. I had the chef's tasting menu and I HIGHLY recommend it! Lets you try a few different dishes that are on the menu, all of which were phenomenal.

Food: A++++

Atmosphere: B (slightly underwhelming, but I like that... it doesn't puff out its chest so to speak and do any "peacocking"... it doesnt need to.  minimalistic, but has a light creole/jazz/Orleans flair. Background music fits the restaurant very well and is at a perfect volume. The emphasis is on the food and honestly you could feed me this food in the middle of a trash dump and I would still give this place 5 stars...)

Service: A+ (very nice friendly knowledgeable. attentive but not in your face. i never felt annoyed with too much waitress interaction (aka "how is everything, do you need more water? blah blah blah".. yet i was never in need of anything. Always had a full glass of water, dirty plates were taken away promptly... very nice)

The price is a little high (about $25) but honestly with out a doubt WORTH IT! Chef tasting menu was $35 - also very...VERY...worth it.

I was really excited to see dim sum in the middle of Pennsylvania. There are Asian restaurants around, but none that make authentic dim sum! 

Unfortunately, this wasn't it. It can't compete with the quality of the dim sum in Philadelphia, Edison (NJ), and NYC. Everything was flavorful but missing the mark. The crystal shrimp dumplings were smaller. The shrimp rice rolls had a thick rice roll. The sticky rice in lotus leaf was not very sticky and felt like it could use another few minutes in the steamer. 

On top of the average food, the service could use some better organization. We waited 20+ minutes for a dish we were told was coming out for us, only to be told in the end that they accidentally gave it to another table. 

In the end, it's still about what I'd expect from a dim sum place in a suburb a good distance from the city. I hope the restaurant gets better organized, because I'd really love to see it succeed!

I don't think they are accepting new customers.  The phone number has been disconnected, however the website is very misleading and appears as if they ARE taking new business.  It's very strange.  I am annoyed.

This is a classic pancake house with friendly staff and warm feel to it. The menu covers all of the basics and the portions are large enough that you could definitely share, depending on how hungry you and your table are. It's a comfortable place to spend a morning, and the price won't break your wallet just for breakfast/brunch. I wish they were open at night for when those "breakfast-for-dinner" cravings hit!

Had the bun.  The pork was really excellent, but the shrimp was not great.  The vermicelli were also much bigger than I've had at other places and I didn't prefer it that way.  Not the greatest I've had in the city, so I wouldn't make a special trip up there when I could just go to Wash Ave.

Update: Went again. Sad dead crab floating in tank. Mushy pho noodles. Won't go again.

I LOVE the new Sidecar bar. Since it was my first time here, I figured, why not order a sidecar (beer with a shot on the side). They have about 6 beers on draft and maybe 15 more in bottles. As a beer snob, I thought they had a good selection. The ambiance is great. While I thought it would be small, it actually felt quite spacious. They have a long bar with seating in addition to both indoor and outdoor seating. It has a very trendy feel, yet at reasonable prices. Very clean and well decorated. All the bartenders were very nice and attentive. I plan to come back to try some of the fancy cocktails!!!

I've been going to this place for years. The NJ version of Border Cafe is "Jose Tejas" and both are ALWAYS PACKED and ALWAYS DELICIOUS. This is the kind of place you can easy wait an hour -- but it's SO worth it!! My go-to dish is a Gold Margherita and a Steak Quesadilla. Fresh warm chips and salsa (which are now spicier than they used to be) are given to each table. LOVE!

Do you have a pulse? Then you must be a fan of pizza. The cat is out of the bag - this place has the best neighborhood pizza in town. Hands down. So flipping good. When you want large pie piled on with toppings this is the place. The crust has always been that perfect not took thick but not too thin. The meat lovers one is our fave

Food: 5/5
Service: 3/5
Venue: 3/5 - a hole in a wall but hey - will travel for food

I LOVE Fresh Kitchen and wish they'd open more locations in Tampa! Anytime I'm in the Westshore district around lunch time, I have to stop here. I always get some variation of the 4 bowl (plenty of food) and one of their delicious frescas to drink. It's usually always crowded at lunch time, but the line moves super quick. Parking can be a little tough, but the Kennedy location has so much more parking than their SoHo location. You order through a line similar to Chipotle and pick your bases, vegetables, protein, add-ons and sauce. Love having this as an option for a quick, healthy lunch!
Had a birthday party for 50 today. Delicious and efficient. Would recommend over n over. The best fish anywhere

Had a dozen raw fresh oysters, potato lyonnaise and a couple of drinks. The oysters were very fresh but some of them still had a little grit left. Potatoes were good and drinks were good. Sat at a table by the window. Seat was amazing with the summer breeze, the elevation, and the street view. If you're going to sit by the window, keep your belongings away from it as it seems like a convenient location to snatch a cell phone. The restaurant was nice and the atmosphere relaxed. The service was great. 
.

I used to go here fairly often in high school before I was diagnosed with celiac disease.  The food is pretty good, and they often have good deals on drinks.  Today, I went with my family for a birthday.  They have reduced the menu significantly since I've last been there, and my favorite thing was the Queso Gringo and chips!  

The service was excellent!  They said that I was their "third gluten allergy person" that they have had, but they were very knowledgeable about my needs.  They were more than willing to accomodate me! Unfortunately, I started munching on chips before inquiring, so now I am more than a little uncomfortable due to cross-contamination in the fryer. While that was my own fault, I don't see myself choosing to go back there anytime soon just because I wasn't super impressed by anything besides the chips, queso, and salsa.  But the service was 5 stars!!!

I was extremely impressed with the TCOB! The staff were welcoming the facilities were pleasant (though could've done without the rap music!) and spotless. I had a lash tint with Amariz, who did a stellar job. Excellent application, no dye in or around my eyes, very attentive to detail. I also had a gel manicure with Sabrina. She took such care to ensure that my manicure was perfect. I've had many manicures and this one is especially nice. No heavy spots, no polish on my cuticles, it's fabulous. I highly recommend the TCOB, it is a great value and the students are very well trained and know what they are doing. Plus they are adorable!

I love this place.  Really.  I'd like to date it--at least one night a week, maybe 3 times as long it isn't TOO needy. It can even have other girlfriends--I like it so much that this time, I would be willing to share.  

I regularly order their products from Green Bean--which is great, but there's something about going to the store and considering ALL the possibilities. Last night, I met friends in the cellar for a little wine, chatting and snacks.  Can anyone say Steak Tartare?  Made right there?  So fresh and delicious...and well, my dog might have just thought that was the best leftover ever--ok, maybe tied with a steak from St. Elmos, but hey, he's a dog.  What does he know?  The cellar is great--a little rustic in design and some fun wine and food to consider as you are spending some time there.  Turns out the more wine I drink, the more I buy.  You think I would have learned this from those promotions where they give you champagne in a department store and next thing I know, I've got 10 new pairs of shoes. 

Okay, so let's see.  Good wine, check.  Amazing selection from the butcher--I was really excited to see Andouille sausage--it's a bit hard to find and being a southern girl, it's a staple in a lot of my favorite recipes so that's a score.  Delicious bacon without the 'crud'...great smoked pork chops and brisket...and much, much more.  Fun pastas, breads, dips and spreads...and even pig ears for the dog.  Pretty sure I  feel a dinner party coming on.  See you soon, Goose.
best coconut cake ever. Besh fish dip too!! I love this place, anytime I have out of town guests I bring them here.
The best!! Amazing staff, excellent vibes, the greatest brews. Can't wait till I go back!! Would recommend to anyone.

Ilir at Time Square is incredible!!! He was very friendly, polite and honest! finally found someone to care in the right manner, for a watch that is becoming a precious heirloom for my boyfriend and me. I plan to bring it here anytime it needs servicing or any other clocks or watches of mine that might need to be repaired. Thank you Ilir, God bless you and your business and I hope you guys are around for many more years to come!

We work on State Street and decided to order take out from Isaac's.  We love to go to the restaurant and bar and decided bring their delicious food to our shop.  The take out food did not disappoint!!!  From beginning to end it was great!  Devon took our order, it was ready to go when they said, and it was delicious!!!  Sometimes take out food isn't as good but clearly Isaac's does NOT have that problem!  They even gave us napkins, utensils and bread without us asking.  Nine out of ten times to-go orders get messed up and this was perfect!!  We will surely be ordering again and I encourage other people to do the same.  Everyone was so friendly, even held the door for us!!!
Yummy, very sweet milk tea. We were disappointed with the doughnut though - it was tough, wasn't sweet at all, and was actually just fried dough. Must try some of the soy/tofu desserts next time!

Zozo's was great!  We went looking for Italian - having just moved to Reno a few weeks ago - and we lucked upon Zozo's after our first choice was closed (Mondays) and we just flat out couldn't find our second choice.  

I'm sooooo glad we came to Zozo's though!  Even though it was a small distance from our house, the ambiance was great for a relaxed Italian joint. 

The service was enthusiastic, prompt, genuine, and helpful.  5 of 5 stars.  I wish I would have asked for our waiter's name before we left, but it truly looked as though all the patrons were being treated just as well as we were.

As for the food - 4 of 5 stars.  The appetizer special - lightly breaded, then fried, artichokes and shrimp with a spicy aoli - was amazing and generously portioned.  The wine selection was varied and easy on the pocketbook.  The salads were as good as one could expect and the entrees pleased as well.  The desserts, however, were complete polar opposites of one another.

My wife's favorite dessert is creme brulee - she gets it almost everywhere we go if it's on the menu.  Me, I tend to take whatever the server recommends, which in this case was the tiramisu.

The raspberry creme brulee was easily one of the three worst creme brulees either of us have ever had.  There was no sugar 'crust' to speak of and the creme was less custard and more soup/wet pudding.  While the raspberry topping looked enticing, it was far too sweet and vastly over-portioned in relation to the rest of the dessert.  We literally took turns bailing it out of the cup with our spoons to save what little good there might be left in the creme.  I'm not trying to be a jerk, but is was seriously awful.   Granted, we ate like half of it because we kept saying too each-other, "It can't really be this bad, right?  Maybe it gets better further down.... " No such luck. 

The tiramisu, however, was easily one the the three BEST either of us had ever had.  I can't even begin to describe the levels of gooey goodness that were layered in those soft pillows of rum-laced heaven! :)

All-in-all, even though it ended on a bit of a down note, we will be back, and likely within a few weeks time.  Zozo's is a great place for a relaxed Italian meal served by people who care and food prepared with a hefty appetite in mind.  

Cin Cin!

My first trip to Miss Saigon was long overdue.  I had been to the other 6 or so Vietnamese restaurants in town first and Miss Saigon for no reason was last.  I saved one of the best for last.  I ordered vermicelli with pork and shrimp.  I have never had this dish before.  It's basically a large bowl of rice noodles with the oils similar so spring rolls with herbs and whatever meat you choose.  Similar to a spring roll bowl type dish.  It was awesome!  The pork and egg rolls were money.  I'm a big eater and couldn't finish.  Other Nashville restaurants may excel more for a bowl of phó from what I saw, but this had the most complete offering of various authentic dishes.  Though there phó didn't look bad in any way.  Come here and try something new.

I wouldnt be writing this review if not for the weird location of Blaze Pizza. 
Directly across from Earth Fare is not where it is.

Anyhoo, I had seen some yelpers write about another branch of this in Citrus Park/WC so after struggling for 45 minutes to find Blaze, I parked and ate here  because I was hungry.

Upon entering, you'll notice the Ford logo emblazoned on top and a plethora of archaic gas pumps , and old fashioned Ford car models. Even the bathroom has sinks made of converted tires which is a gas. There is an indoor and patio seating which is nice. In the center is the bar.

They specialize in burgers and traditional American fare. They have a wide selection of beers and mixed drinks. I got the 'Merica Mule (MURRICA!) which was $10. It was very refreshing.  4/5

I decided to go with the Estate Burger . It sounded nice from the description. The patty was well seasoned and juicy. The best part about it was the bacon aoili and jam that gave it a sweet tang to offset the savory patty.    4/5

Madison was my server and she was very friendly and gave me recommendations on what to order. 

There aren't any glaring negatives, but note that this has classic American rock songs being played and is a bit noisy. I think this is good for families and "the boys" , but less of an intimate date place.

Marker 39 is our absolute favorite!! The freshest ingredients and impeccable execution of all their dishes. Every. Single. Time!! We're always hesitant to try something different than what we order before because everything we have is our new favorite But we always do and Chef Justin never disappoints! The service alike. Our go to girl is jamie but the whole team is truly versed in their cuisine and wine knowledge. Jamie always has the perfect wine pairing for our meal. Always timely and consistent in all areas! Marker 39 is a must! 

Everything is still so amazing. Service is on point as usual. We come at least once a week and they never disappoint. Jamie and her staff are an absolute delight. You never have to wait for anything. Justin's food is next to none. Everything he touches turns to gold. Thanks again, marker 39!!

I don't think I could find one negative thing to say about this place even if I tried!!  I don't even know where to start.  OK let's start with the food, absolutely AMAZING!  I was in the mood for steak so I had the churrasco, I was going to eat 1/2 and take the rest home....yeah that didn't happen.  The meat was seasoned and cooked perfectly, just the right touch of authentic chimichurri on top and the salsa they serve with it is to die for.  I was trying to keep it a little on the lighter side since I was breaking a juice fast with this meal so I got the green salad as a side, even the salad was excellent, FRESH field greens with just the right amount of everything including crispy plantain chips on top as croutons and served with mayo/ketchup dressing(sounds basic I know....not at all).  I did order the Epanandas as an appetizer just to taste one, they are typically a tell tale sign if you know what you are doing and man do they know what they doing alright, the where so homemade tasting and also served with that dressing.  Yummy!  Next time the Bacalaitos!  I'm normally not a dessert person but here I  wanted to order dessert so bad but I didn't but did have the Cafe con Leche and so glad I did, probably the best I ever had!!  The Staff, now this is the way you should be treated at every restaurant you go to.  They were all one friendlier than the other.  From the minute I walked in I felt comfortable, they were very friendly and you immediately got the family-like vibe.  My waitress Melanie was knowledgable, very nice and gave just the right amount of attention.  Another waiter even checked with me to see if all was ok.  After my meal one of the owners Orlando came out introduced himself, made sure that everything was perfect and shook my hand.  The atmosphere is cozy, place is immaculate, decor is nice and the music completes it, they have a nice outside seating area(which I typically love) but it was too hot!  This is the kind of place that has you looking at the menu thinking about what you are going to order next time you are there, like this week...LOL  Grandma Seafood Soup and gotta try the Trifongo!!!

I showed for my scheduled appointment and no one was at the front counter. After about ten minutes someone came in and asked who my appointment was with. When I replied Zoe, she said good luck with that- she was an hour late yesterday. I waited for what was 30 minutes past appointment time and left. No one ever called, I was a monthly customer for almost a year. I think I've found a replacement groomer elsewhere but still surprised how this ended.

Renamed to Crown and Bull. New signs not up yet. You can find it by looking for the Bulldog face with a Crown on it head. Food was great. Waitress (Rebecca) suggested half/half order of the French Toast special and the in restaurant made corned beef Benedict. Lots of food and fantastic tasting.

I bought a living social deal for a color, cut and conditioning treatment. My appointment was at 5 pm on a Friday. I was looking forward to getting my hair done and then going out for dinner. I arrived at the salon and was shocked to see the condition of the salon. It was dirty and so outdated. I did not realize that most of the clientele were older individuals. Not that that matters but I definitely felt out of place. I was introduced to my stylist Chris who said she would be with me shortly. She said the client before me was late for her appointment so consequently Chris was running late but I would not have to wait that long. She asked another staff member to do my conditioning treatment first. I found this odd but I don't know, I'm not a hair stylist. Apparently the other staff member found it odd as well and told me that she didn't understand why Chris was having her do this first but proceeded to do it anyway. The staff member applying my treatment was complaining about having to stay late and did not make my conditioning treatment very relaxing. I was then placed under a hair dryer to process my treatment. I sat for over 30 minutes while Chris finished the other client's hair cut and styling. She took her dear sweet time, exchanging photos with the other client. I understand wanting to be nice to clients and make them feel welcomed but I was so annoyed because it was not my fault the other client was late and so I should not have had to wait until an hour after my appointment to actually get to start my color. Finally Chris had me sit at her station and we talked about what I wanted. She was very nice and talkative and agreed to do a low light instead of a high light. The next almost 2 hours consisted of low lights, processing, shampooing, gloss, and a lot of waiting and a lot of listening to Chris blab about everything. She did offer me a drink and was polite. She wanted me to make sure I knew it did not inconvenience her to have to stay late. I was thinking: really??? You are inconveniencing me because you were an hour late to our appointment! I ended up having to change my reservations for dinner because it took over 3 hours for her to finish my hair. The color was barely noticeable. I was very disappointed. When I went to work on Monday, everyone asked me what I had done because they did not notice a difference. She did do a nice job on the cut and style though. By the time I left I was so annoyed and I did not ever want to come back so I just didn't say anything about how disappointed I was in the color. I did tip her and bought some product. 

In summation, I will NEVER go back here nor recommend this place to anyone. They really need to update the decor and hire a cleaning crew or something. Yes, the staff was nice but the work was poor and I felt like I wasted over 3 hours and did not have a relaxing salon experience.
Still finding their way.  Drinks miss the mark, meat heavy on the fat, be careful.  Having been to Cuba quite disappointed!

It is hard not to give Fogo 5 stars, if not purely on value for the money.  Dinner for two guys, no appetizer, no dessert, no liquor, $148.00 with tip.  You say that sounds kinda high and make no mistake that's not pocket change.  But let me explain.

No apps- well no, the "more impressive than most places entire menu" salad bar comes with your meal.  I had capris I salad, taboulah, nova lox, hearts of palm and charcuterie.  That's app enough for anyone.

 O alcohol- yep, that stuff ruins your tastebuds, keep a clean pallet with water and tea.  Salty meats and stuff need water to chase them.

No dessert - I was absurdly stuffed.  The Grilled bananas come out with your meal and beat dessert at most places.

The steak, chicken pork and steak and lamb and did I mention steak come out hot and fast.  Unlimited in amounts, so pace yourself to get to the filet and the lamb.  This is the only place I will even touch sir loin and it is absolutely fabulous.

Value for your dollar, incredible, I have spent more and gotten far far less.

This place was delicious. It's family-style small plates, so we got a number of different things for the group. Hits were the burrata appetizer, the Stache flatbread, and the affogato. Service was good. The interior of this place is adorable - perfect for a date night or fancy-ish night with friends. Definitely worth the trip, just be prepared to spend a little extra dough!

Don't waste your time on this gas station. They claim to be a truck stop but they don't allow customers to use their restroom even if they buy gas there. The staff was very mean, told us to drive down the road to find restrooms

This is a good Asian place; not your typical Chinese. The chef/owner is from South China bordering Burma, so her flavors of noodles and various sauces are unique. Love the collection of local Ski sodas. They could be a bit more hygienic.
Nice atmosphere and excellent service. Beef short rib was really good and beet salad was surprisingly tasty.

This store is the worst. The general manager Jesus borders between unprofessional and a criminal. When dealing with an issue that required the manager, he literally said "I don't care about you or HD policy, I need to make money". Luckily corporate resolved the issues. As a result, I took a year break from any HD shopping. Recently found that 2 other locations (Holiday & Gulf-to-Bay) are actually peopled with nice employees. I now do 98% of my shopping at Lowes & Ace, but only when they do not have what I need I will occasionally shop HD online and only use the HD card incase I encounter another nut job store manager. I use to be in this HD at least 3 times a week. Now Ace & Lowes get all my business.
I have gone to Steve for years.   He's fixed several cars.  The cars always look great and he is fast and makes the process of dealing with insurance a breeze.
One of the best Philly cheesesteaks I have ever had.  Highly recommend  I was with a friend who is from Philly and he also said it was really really good.   :-)

I highly recommend Derek and the team at Service Masters. Derek was very attentive and explained to me throughly the pros and cons of resurfacing vs. replacing my rotars on my brakes. He took great care of my truck! Overall I highly recommend them and will visit them again. Lastly, their pricing was very affordable and more reasonable than the dealership.

I live close to this place.  I have visited it just once.  It's quite a decent sized restaurant and supposedly one of the best breweries in town (which I didn't try since I don't drink) and I tried fish tacos for lunch.  They were quite fresh and well made.  The service was adequate and timely.  Price are OK.

This place is great!  Heading up I-55 with two young boys, we were looking for an alternative to drive-thrus or Cracker Barrel, and gave the Butterfly Patio a shot.  So happy we did - we all loved our food and the service was fast and friendly.  Highlights were the House Salad and Beer Beef Stew, but the sandwiches were also delicious.  We didn't notice any FDA, OSHA, INS, HIPAA, or any other violation - just good flavors and fresh ingredients.  ;-)

The food is very good, but unless it's Happy Hour, the drink prices are a little steep.  The cheapest wine by the glass is $9 and beers start at $6 but most at $7.  Come during Happy Hour though and drinks are half off and snacks 3 for $12.  Pretty good drink specials at that point, 3:00-6:00.  

We ordered the hummus, bruschetta, and tuna snacks.  Hummus dip was terrific but pita was just ok, kinda hard and room temperature.  The dip was artichoke based which was interesting and had a nice flavor that you wouldn't expect.  The bruschetta was good but nothing special with the tomato looking kinda old.  The tuna was great, over a tiny cup of salad.  I would have loved this a salad/meal. After devouring this dish as an appetizer I was surely craving more.

We also ordered a burger, crab cake salad and gnocchi.  The burger was a nice meal with the shoestring fries but pretty typical.  The gnocchi were terrific and unexpectedly large.  Add in some chicken or chorizo and you'll be full for sure.  The crab cake salad would be a nice refreshing lunch option but for dinner I think it would have been presented better as an appetizer.  Very good and large, but over a pretty bland "salad" with just a bed of arugula and crab cake.  Sounds more like a crab cake with a side of greens to me.

There's plenty of bar seating and a nice patio area at Old Granite Street Eatery.  Service is slow as there didn't seem like there were many people working there on a weekday at 6:00pm, but once we ordered we got our food and drinks at a reasonable pace.  Getting the check taken care of took a bit longer than we wanted, but overall the pace of the meal was fine and the food filling and good quality all around.  Total bill came to about $90 with 2 drinks each, 1 on Happy Hour a piece.  I would think their brunch is better than their dinner with such a nice patio so I would recommend giving that a try.
Food incredible we sat at the counter. We had great service. It's a definite breakfast stop.

Really a nice place, in a good location. Its in Ybor City, which is a pretty historic little part of town. Its at the end of the "strip",  within walking 
distance, 6-8 blocks worth, of all sorts of clubs, bars and restaurants,
so there is plenty to do at night, and I am sure, into the early hours of 
the morning. Some of the local buildings are a little rundown, so its 
kind of looking like they aren't really sure what to do with the area. 

Anyway, the hotel is very nice, clean, quiet, its got a small fitness center, small pool, serves a breakfast that is one of the better that I 
have seen in hotels, with juice, coffee, cereal, yogurt, muffins, danish,
fruit, and usually some kind of hot entree, bacon, eggs, ham, etc.
So, you can really pack up on breakfast before heading out. Its within
a $10 or so cab ride to the port, the St Pete Times Forum, the 
Aquarium and across the street from a trolley that will take you a lot
of those places for $2 each way, $4 for a day pass. Plus the hotel
has a free shuttle to go within 5 miles of the hotel, for free, that goes
first come, first served. 

And its close to the airport, about a 15-20 minute ride at most, even
during morning-drive, and the cost was about $20, not  including
a tip.

Food was good. Just FYI - you have to use your personal phone to access the menu and place your order. There is a QR code on every table. If you don't have an iPhone or a QR code reader, you'll need to download one of those. Then you place your order from their app - and you pay AND leave a tip before you ever see your food. I was not really sure why I needed to tip someone when all they did was deliver my order and fill my water glass. Also there's a pre-checked "COVID Relief" fee when you are checking out on your phone. Its like $1.66, the note says "to help keep our kitchen open" but aren't I already paying for that with my order? Unless you want me to believe that a savory pancake actually costs $10 to make... Plus there's the tip - I mean, who gets that? The cook? The guy pouring water? The guy who explained how to order and pay (would have been more useful to explain the food). The owner? Anyway, a bit too much work and money for just ok food and zero service. Oh and, there is no outdoor dining, unless sitting on the edge of a parking lot is what you're looking for. Inside the tables are sufficiently far apart, unless you want to have a semi-private conversation. The dining room is set up like a cafeteria, so you're going to hear everyone's conversations and they are going to hear yours. Yeah overall. needs improvement.

A fun, quaint little distillery. So happy to see another in the downtown area! Love the drinks and the price point is very reasonable. My friends and I make the most out of the games and popcorn. Looking forward to being back soon.

With their great bagels and sandwiches, I want to really like Spread. But their customer service is awful. 

I've been to Spread about 5 times now and every time, I've gotten lots of attitude from whoever is behind the counter. Example: 

Me: "how's your special?" (The one posted on the "SPECIAL" sign as soon as you walk in.)

Girl: "uh we have lots of specials." 

Then I said in the same order I wanted coffee. This was discussed with the other peach of a twenty-something counter girl. Original said, "you didn't say you wanted coffee." 

Anonymous man behind me in line: "She said she wanted coffee." 

And this has gone on, and on, and on. And, scene.

Last night, my mom and I chose New Deck as the meeting place for drinks and a bite after her conference nearby. The menu was exactly what we were looking for; a decent happy hour and a few small plates. I had French onion soup and we shared a Mediterranean plate and some chicken fingers. The beers were super fresh and delicious; Guinness for Mom and Harp for me. 

New Deck has a nice pub environment and it was clean and pretty bustling considering the Monday night. However, New Deck has a problem, and it's pretty clearly outlined in other recent reviews. It's the service. We sat at the bar and the bartender was surlier than Mr. Carson in Downton Abbey, and not in an endearing way. An Irish accent only gets you so far. It was very hard to get this bartender's attention on multiple occasions, and we actually felt like we were bothering him when we needed something. This is the guy you stick behind the bar on a college campus? 

New Deck filled all of our requirements for a night out except for the good service part. We'll be choosing another destination next time.

This place has easily the worst service of any establishment in the history of establishments.  They are the Comcast of coffee.  Sadly, I'm a regular at soy and go almost everyday since July 2016.  It's at least a 10 minute wait for a coffee.  Yes, 10 minute minimum to put coffee in the cup.  But don't worry, the employees will look very busy while they ignore you.   Decided today, after waiting 20 minutes for the coffee, that I'm never coming here again.

Caesar chicken salad--lousy. Staff-completely inattentive or robotic. Told server how lousy the food was with specificity (bad lettuce/rubbery watered down chicken parts--gross) as she threw the entire salad away! No bother to offer something different, essentially spent $25 on a glass of wine. Not looking for free food, just food that was edible! Robotic server....in her 20's asking me at least 5 times over the course of 45 minutes none if I would like another wine--perhaps a second glass would have made the food taste better. And really, referring to me as "hon"--I am in my 50s--weird!  Bad experience all around! Again--the salad was disgusting!  So wish I had eaten somewhere else!

Hi expectations, nightmarish lunch. Looked like a great venue, but service was really bad.  Waited 20 min just to get the check, then had to flag down another waiter to get my check. Food was just typical mex chicken fajita, fine,,,but staff up!

The food was good and on time. I appreciate that it was no contact delivery. The chips and guacamole were great. You could tell the chips are fried in house and the guacamole is made fresh as well. The tacos were good definitely delicious and perfect for ordering out. The chicken tacos tasted fresh and made in house. I will definitely be ordering from this place in the future.
This is a cute place, you can sit outside. The food is really good and the owners are very friendly. I have eaten there about 5x and got food to go I highly recommend this place for soup & sandwich
Had the peel and eat shrimp appetizer with fish and chips. Can't go wrong coming here for lunch or dinner.
Really great food.  Excellent bar with amazing cocktails by Ethan! Beautiful restaurant ambiance.  Located close to Murat and Lucas Oil Stadium. .

I know I update this review somewhat frequently, but I like to reiterate that the staff is consistently knowledgeable and helpful. 

I went in pending a break tag check completion since my passenger side brake light was out and the folks at the inspection center suggested I go to Autozone. Rolled up with not much of a line and little wait. I approached the counter with my car make, model, and year and let them know I needed a brake light. 

The gentlemen then came out and installed the light in seconds. I could've maybe have figured this out after a few How-To YouTube video but it was incredibly convenient for him to do it. The cost of the light was around $10 and I have the other bulb just in case the other ones goes out. He also asked if there was anything else that I wanted to check before I went back including other lights and systems just in case. 

If you have a problem with your car, make sure to know the make, model and year so they can expeditiously find the part for you. I also say bring a few extra dollars to tip as a kind gesture!

This place is good for a Panda. Food quality is consistant and staff is fast and friendly.
Outdoor seating is nice in the summer but a bit load with the road right there.
Walk in customers definitely take a back seat to drive through customers as they feed probably 3 drive through orders for every walk in. Needs to change for sure. It feels really rude.

PLEASE folks, don't buy from this dealership.
THIS IS ESPECIALLY TRUE, if it's the only option left for you.
They deal in dishonest, coercive, intimidating, push and rapacious consumer relation tactics. Covering themselves in stipulations/ claused jargons that would just blow your mind as the every day person.

PLEASE read any fine print or anything they offer you before you sign, and date anything.

DON'T listen to absolutely anything they say, take it all with a grain of salt; and might as well go in there with an attorney to interpret the nonsense they spew if you absolutely must! And insists on dealing with them.

You my friends have been warned, happy shopping.
Strictly based off my experience, both past & present dealings with GoHonda.

Service at its best.  At this point they have all of my business -- eyelashes, facials, waxing, pedicures. Prices are fair and quality of work is superb.  Facilities are very clean and it's so relaxing!  It seems like every service comes with a complimentary massage. What a luxury!

CenturyLink can't seem to figure out how to actually cancel accounts. I had called them to cancel and the customer servive rep assured me that everything was confirmed and they'd be sending the final bill. After a few days, I was notified that they had taken a full month's charge out of my account some time after my alleged cancellation.

Lo and behold, they never actually cancelled anything. I had to reach out via their social media chat for help (and in-writing confirmation) cancelling my service for real this time. 

CenturyLink was an overcharged sub-par servive while I was using them and the only thing as lackluster as their Internet speeds and connection reliability is their customer service.

EDIT: To their credit, the social media team did everything correct in helping me. The account is closed and I did recieve payment for what was wrongly taken. It shouldn't have taken this much effort to finally have things settled, but it's through no fault of the social media support team-- they were very responsive and helpful and I reccomend this means of contact for anyone facing similar issues.

3 of my coworkers and I decided to have lunch here based on many reviews we had read.  We arrived around 11:45 and the lone customer was finishing her lunch.  I noticed at least 5 employees to the 4 of us, so we seemed primed to have great customer service and a great experience.  My 3 coworkers ordered while I was trying to decide what I wanted. When I was ready, I approached the counter to order, where I waited for a solid 5 minutes before someone finally asked if I had been helped (all the while I was making eye contact with all of the other employees).  I ordered the pastrami sandwich (which on the menu board said was $10).  The employee rang me up and gave me the total of nearly $14.  No drink.  No side.  Just the sandwich which the menu said was $10.  (I later talked to one of my coworkers who was there and they thought they were overcharged as well).  I politely asked if I could substitute fried onions instead of the red onions that come on the sandwich, as I am not partial to red onions.  The employee went to the cook (who was literally 15 feet away from me and facing me) to relay my request, which was greeted with an obvious rolling of the eyes and snort of derision.  My sandwich came out as requested.  The marble rye was very good, I must say.  However, the pastrami was dry as a bone.  I have had pastrami in many different places and I know that it can be tricky to get super lean cuts to be moist and tender.  However, this was dry and chewy, not at all what should be expected from how this establishment touts its fare.  The cherry on top of the meal was when the cook walked by the 4 of us and made a snide remark about how these sandwiches were her beloved creations, inferring that any alteration to them was a direct affront to her. If you have that much of an aversion to substitutions, simply say, "Sorry, no substitutions, please." and let that stand on its own.  I guess we checked the box on PRB. Not likely to return, even for the butchery services, which is a shame.

The owners are fantastic and really care about their customers! Everything on the menu is delicious too. Make sure you ask for/try the chipotle chicken ranch wrap ( on the spicy side). Their salads are awesome and they come in sizes to split or feed a crowd!

The food just is not good. I tried twice. The first time I had the salmon. I wasn't convinced it wasn't actually chicken. The vegetables in the stir fry tasted rotten. I picked around until I gave up. Then second night, I decided to meet them where they are and order bar food. The chicken fingers were sinewy and the breading was weak. The sautéed spinach tasted like old spinach and old oil. I couldn't bear trying it a 3rd time.

My friend didn't join me for my meals, but had breakfast there one day. Based on my feedback, she was pleasantly surprised. The egg was cooked fine but the croissant was a bit greasy. Coffee was drinkable. If that's pleasant, your standards need reviewimg.

In the end, I navigated away from the hotel for the rest of my meals and found some real gems in the unassuming neighborhood. Venture out and you won't be let down.

Took a really wonderful class there this morning. I'll start by saying I've practiced yoga for about 15 years and I'm a certified instructor who's taught in her past life. However, since moving to Tucson about a year and a half ago, I let go of my yogi self. Instead I've been taking lots of kickboxing and circuit training classes, which has been a fun adventure, but has also been really hard on my joints. I've found myself with a very sore lower back lately, stiff joints, tight muscles, and a serious need for a yoga fix. I tried Barefoot's yin classes a couple of times, which were pretty good, but I was totally blown away by today's "yoga basics" class now being offered. The instructor managed to make one posture last the entirety of class (besides a warm-up and savasana), yet it still felt challenging. She broke it down in a way that rivals most workshops I've been to, but managed not to lose the yogic philosophy component in the midst of the spot-on physical instruction. It was a great yoga refresher and my SI joint somehow felt better than it has in months upon leaving. Will definitely be back.

Very interesting vibe to this place - It's like going to a hipster bar in Little Tokyo. 

Service was excellent - we got a hot towel before we ordered, which was a very nice touch. 

Food is amazing - started with the JFC (Japanese tried chicken) as an appetizer, which was spicy and delicious. The signature ramen is obviously great.. It's nice that they have a vegetarian option as well, which I've never seen in other ramen houses. I tried this one and it was just simply delicious. 

It's a great stand out place in Nashville where it's tough to get away from Southern food. 5 stars!!!

Food is always fresh and delicious. I make it a point to stop here every time I go to Chinatown. If it wasn't cash only, I'd definitely buy more. Sometimes I don't carry cash because, you know, credit cards. 

Sponge cake is a favorite of mine from KC Pastries. Staff is always friendly here.

4:21 p.m. Sushi person is there. Ask to get a California roll with shrimp instead of imitation crab meat (because my wife has an allergic to it). He was running low on white rice and was unwilling to make more. Really...it's not even dinner time. Voiced my complaint with Ken (manager on duty), who was very nice and apologized. The sushi people lease this space from Landis. Maybe Landis should find new sushi people. This doesn't make them look good!
Generally quite good though not always awesome. Highly recommend a chef's box. $16 for salmon one is huge.

I am so upset with Reeves Volkswagen. Specifically the advisor Melissa. I made an appointment to get my car serviced on Friday. When I drove to Tampa and dropped it off they then told me it might take up until Monday to get it fixed but they would call me on Friday to let me know the cost and how long it would take. Nobody ever called me, I then tried to call on Sunday but they apparently are not open on the weekends which no one told me. So Monday morning I sit on hold for thirty minutes trying to get a hold of Melissa because even though I have never spoken to this woman she is the ONLY person in this entire place of business that can help me. She then tells me she'll call me back and let me know. She doesn't. So I called back again and Melissa is busy but I was told she'll call me back. I highly doubt it. Don't know when I'll get my car back. Don't know how much it will be. It's going on four days to get it serviced. I'm livid. Horrible customer service and terrible design with the "advisors".

Also, the excuse I keep hearing is that they're backed up. Okay well stop booking appointments if you're not going to be able to get to my car for 3 days. This is absolutely ridiculous I wish I had taken my car anywhere else.

So good! We've been 4 or 5 times, and it's consistently amazing. We've tried almost all the pizzas - love love love the Selma, but they are all delicious! Well worth the 20 minute drive from Nashville. My favorite part though - the chocolate chip cookie skillet. No matter how full we are, there is always room for that! It's got a great vibe and is family friendly. Love this place!!

The Greek chicken was absolutely spectacular and comes with so much food. Also the Italian beef is about as close as I've found anywhere to what you can get in downtown Chicago. It's real close and also a TON of food. The fry sauce caused me to eat ALL of my fries and I don't even like fries. Love this place and the prices are great.

I've been waiting for a GREAT coffee shop to arrive in West Kenstington for a couple of years and this is IT.   I only wish the hours were expanded. They do a great job with the coffee-it's really consistent.  I've sat for a couple of hours doing work w/o interruption, and that's a real bonus. Other times, I've been able to chat with other locals who also love this spot. 

The other day I was running late from an appointment and JUST made it at 4pm as they were locking up. One of the owners saw me in my car and waved me in for the last cup of the day. Now that's customer service! I wish them the best of luck..

Ate there for the first time on July 8th. Many friends had raved about it and I finally made a point of going. It was very good. Had the fresh rolls and the Lemongrass Tofu.  (it's Lemongrass Chicken on the menu but they will substitute). Quite a nice selection of vegetarian items. (I'm not a vegetarian, but have many friends who are.)

Beer and wine is available - I opted for a Tiger Beer - from Singapore.

Was surprised how small the place was. I can imagine there is frequently a wait, given how popular it seems to be.  That would be my main concern in returning - hate to have to wait.

Staff seemed very friendly - knew many of the repeat visitors by name.

Had a rather big-city "feel" to it, if that makes any sense. And I mean that in a good way!

If you like Asian food, give it a try!
Quick service, everything was sooo yummy. Just wish it was like the old days with 4 piece rolls so I could order more. #4piecerollsrule

DO NOT EXPECT YOUR DEPOSIT BACK NO MATTER HOW IMMACULATE YOU KEEP THE HOME.
My family and I lived in a rental property managed by The Nordstrom Group for 5 years. They are great while you are renting with them for the most part but lack compassion and basic human decency, for example while we lived there the home got broken into with the door being kicked down and they took 2 weeks to replace the front door so our family was living in an unsafe environment through that time. If minor issues arise they are quick to get them taken care of as long as you stay on them about it BUT they are awful once it's time to move. 
I was given a 30 day notice that the house would be put up for sale and we had to move. That in it self is frustrating but at the time I had just had twins who were living in the NICU so it couldn't have come at a worse time. They could not have been less empathetic to our situation. So we did what we had to do and scrambled to move out in time. 
We kept that place in great condition we repainted the house interior every year, and had the carpets professionally cleaned every 6 months or so (and freshly done for the move), we reported every issue we ever had with the house and got things promptly taken care of.  We cleaned the house very well when we moved out with the exception of the oven and a couple of tiny crumbs left in a kitchen drawer and on the floor in front of it because my toddler was eating as I was waiting for Vanessa to arrive for inspection. I figured it wasn't a big deal and they could take it out of our nearly TWO THOUSAND DOLLAR deposit. I was wrong. Vanessa came to inspect and said they would need to have a cleaning service go in and re clean the entire house because of the crumbs left. She was extremely rude and passive aggressive with comments like "I understand your babies are in the hospital but this place is unacceptable, it truly is filthy your husband should have hired a professional cleaner if you couldn't get it done." When it came time for the deposit not only did they refuse to give it back but they tried to charge me $500 more for 2 air filters to be replaced when I just replaced them 3 months prior!
