So I asked for them to compare the home to when I was given the keys at move in. I wrote down every issue with the home how the walls were filthy, how they left ice in the sink and a full plate of food in the microwave, and crumbs and stains everywhere on the tile  along with tons of pet hair but they refused to do a comparison. Funny thing is in their listing of the home they mentioned how well maintained the home was kept and how move in ready it was using the photos they took during inspection. 
The Nordstrom Group is not a place I'd recommend to anyone they scam you out of your money for the simple reason that they can get away with it. It's a moral-less company with zero integrity.

Typically, I'm not one to get all excited over Greek for lunch.  Let's just say, I'm not in a hurry to get anyone to the Greek.  Not sure why.  Maybe it's because I just don't get tingly when I hear the word gyro.  Also, I don't eat veal, or lamb.  Simply because they (calves and lambs) are just too cute to consume.  Combine this with the suggestion of a friend who goes to the same sandwich place each and every day for lunch, and I'm like "Dude, you eat the same sandwich every day, of course a new place is going to taste good." So I never took Zoya's seriously. 

ADD side note, if anyone ever wants to open their own sandwich shop, here's a free name idea.  Hawgwarts Sandwitches and Sandwizards.  Make sure you spell it Hawgwarts for legal purposes.

Back on track here...Well today I gave in, and said "Brah, you can pick any place you want brah."  I throw "brah" around liberally.  I also chew my gum with my mouth open, and over extend my jaw whilst in chew brah.  There you have it, I threw him a low hanging curve ball, and whammo.... he hit it to Zoya's for the home run of lunches.  I will admit, I yelped the place before going so I knew it wasn't going to suck based on the reviews.  I'm happy I went, because I now have a killer place to go for my change-of-pace lunch.

So why do they get a 5 star from me?  Well that's really easy.  The food is great! The gyro is plump (not all dry and blah), and the Greek salad is off the chain.  Haven't tried the baklava, but it looked good as all Hades.  They also get your food out relatively quickly, which is nice as well.  Another great thing is their lunch deal.  Greek lunch for 9.99 which includes a plump gyro, off the chain salad, soda, and bread.  It's quite filling, and relatively more healthy than 5 Guys Clogged Arteries, and Fries.  Zoya's lunch is actually less expensive based on what you order.

Another ADD Side note...  My prediction is that those who routinely eat on the west side of Olive, and New Ballas are likely to live longer compared to those who eat on the east.  This is purely speculation, and not the reviews of Yelp and their affiliates.  This comment does not guarantee longevity.  

Ironically though, the name Zoya means "life" in Greek.  BOOM!  Mind is blown...

Oh, Han Dynasty, you broke my heart...

I'd been wanting to try Han Dynasty for years, but never seemed to get around to it, so my hubby and I booked a reservation and headed down to Olde City.  We arrived and waited... and waited.... and waited.  We waited for 45 minutes, which wouldn't be a huge deal if we hadn't made a reservation.  The hostess was completely inept and would walk away from the podium for long periods of time, during which we saw several other potential customers leave out of frustration.  When we finally sat down, the manager apologized for the wait and offered to get us each a drink on the house (very nice).  However, when he came back, he threw two beers (the cheapest kind they serve, I should note) down on the table and ran off.  Since I don't drink beer, I tried to flag him down and when I finally got his attention, ordered a glass of wine.  He short-poured the wine (poor form, Han Dynasty, poor form--why offer a free drink, if you're not willing to oblige?) 

Anyways, though we were annoyed, we wanted to give the food a fair shot since we'd been hearing raves for so long.  The Dan-Dan noodles are very good--a solidly 4 star dish with some kick.  We were severely disappointed by our entrees though.  The dry pot beef was incredibly average and the crispy rice chicken was inedible because it was so sweet (and just plain bad).  Han, I had such high expectations for us, but it's clear that we just weren't meant to be.

The interior of my Subaru Legacy had not been cleaned other than a superficial vacuuming for two years. Brandon took about four hours and did a truly superior job. For $90. My wife of 25 years come tomorrow has high standards. She will not be disappointed. Thank you, Brandon

Unfortunately for the wait staff, my meal was actually quite delicious (chicken penne) but I have to give this restaurant 2 stars because of the waiter we experienced at our table. I was part of a fairly large group (8) people tonight for a friends birthday. From the start, the waiter seemed annoyed that we were a large group, despite the fact that the restaurant only had about 6-8 other tables currently occupied with several other waiters/waitresses present. The waiter consistently made rude comments/remarks when seemingly simple requests were made (requesting a soup when he asked for appetizer orders and denying two people at our table extra eel/spicy mayo sauce because he gave a small side sauce cup to one person already). Additionally, at the end of our meal, the waiter ran after two different people in our party regarding the total paid amount after tip when they did not factor in the suggested tip amount. Overall, I did enjoy my meal, but would not return due to the service received.

Sam did my hair and makeup for my wedding on May 19 as well as my bridesmaids. She was amazing. She arrived on time on the wedding day and is very professional!! She knows up to date and modern ways to do hair and makeup. My bridesmaids loved her too! I looked amazing on my wedding day because of her. If she is any indication of how the rest of the stylist are, they must all be amazing!  I would recommend TEAM to anyone in the Santa Barbara area!

We love jets pizza!  They have such great pizza and so many different options to accompany your pizza.  Options such as chicken, breadsticks and even salad!  Gluten free available as well.  Great local goto spot for us.
Everything on the menu is fresh and delicious. I'm a sucker for the lobsta roll and clam chowder.

A Small dining area accompanied by French music, we have been to Bibou twice. Both times we had the same knowledgeable waiter. He was on point with describing anything on the menu in case you are unsure what they are serving. He also was familiar with how light or rich each dish was. The first time we went to Bibou, we were able to order the chicken liver mousse, escargot, lobster bisque and foie gras for starters. Each dish was extremely flavorful! The second time we went, we ordered a cantaloupe salad and braised beef tongue. The cantaloupe wasn't anything to die for but still tasty nonetheless. The beef tongue was light and tender. We also had the bone marrow entree, filet mignon and purple potato encrusted halibut. All dishes were cooked to perfection and flavorful with each bite. We finished off dinner with frozen chocolate made with Grand Marnier. Each bite tasted like orange liqueur followed by rich dark chocolate. If you plan on dining here, plan ahead of time as reservations need to made a few weeks in advance or hope for any cancellations.

While in town visiting Philly, this was already on my list of places to eat and I wanted to leave this place as the final place for dinner before we head home Sunday and this place DID NOT DISAPPOINT!! It's hard to find vegan places where you can dress up a little, have the ambience of fine dining and great food all in one, but I promise you, this is your place!! We sat at the bar and staff was so nice and food was incredibly delicious...Hubby is still talking about it! We're from Maryland and they are opening up a restaurant in DC (Tasty Radish I think) and we cannot wait!
United's been a good carrier for me.  Especially glad to get home to SF after a long biz trip.  The terminals always have decent food options, and the staff usually are quite helpful.

Got there early around 5 on a Saturday and glad we did as it got packed fast. Great atmosphere. Fast service. We tried the veggie ball, classic, beef and turkey. Amazing balls and even more amazing sauces. Also had the potatoes and they were addicting. Can't wait to come back.

Warning: Serving sizes are huge. We made the mistake of ordering the pulled pork poutine as an appy to share and it was amazing but so much that we almost weren't hungry for dinner which was a shame when we saw the size of our burgers. My husbands burger was stacked high with several different types of meat and onion rings. I had the chicken sandwhich and it was also had tons of chicken. The prices here are a little high but when you see how much meat you get they really are not too bad at all!
The pizza Is great and the service was great and the people were nice and it might be the best place I have ever eaten at!!!!

Just checked out the Enjoy Centre for the first time to see Glow as well as eat at The Glasshouse Bistro. The food was awesome! I had this beat salad that was almost too pretty to eat and my husband had a burger with these amazing fries! I also had a hot chocolate and him a latté. Everything tasted really good. I thought the prices on especially the drinks were a little high but it all tasted good! The greenhouse portion was pretty. Lots of plants out, even in winter. The Glow event was super cool to see. It was pricey but when you see it (I can't imagine what their power bill is!!!), you can see the reasoning for the price. The Christmas store was alright. I thought there were more vendors than there was. So much of the stuff was for kids and babies! If you're looking for a date night, fun for the kids, or some awesome photo opportunities, I would definitely recommend checking it out!
Food is wonderful, service is great. Menu is easy to read. This place is my go-to for authentic Korean food.
Service was terrible, wings weren't very hot yet we waited 40 minutes for out food, wish we would've went elsewhere. What a waste of money

After 5 visits to repair my 4 year old washing machine the job still is NOT done!!! If I could give negative stars I would. 2 of these visits never even had to happen as the tech only walked in and said he was going to order parts and turned around walked out. Are you kidding me? He could have called me and told me that over phone and never bothered coming out to waste my day waiting for him. But NO he made me wait the entire 4 hours and then showed up as the last appt. of the day and after 6:30pm at night - while my husband were in the middle of eating dinner!!! The tech convinced me to purchase the add'l warranty agreement as it would cover any &  all parts that would need to be replaced and would be way cheaper than purchasing a new machine.... Ummmm ok. I was convinced that I was going to have to purchase a new machine. Guess that's what I should have done in the first place as that's what I have to do anyway and I would have saved myself 6 weeks worth of frustration!!!! Sears you have lost all respect. You are definitely not the company, nor are your products what they use to be!!!

It's like a whole foods corner store.  Not as expensive and a pretty good selection of fresh produce.  It's perfect for a quick grocery stop for organic items without the crowd.  TFM label almond milk is delish.

My favorite hotel in Philly. I travel a lot for work and this is one of my favorites in the U.S.  The rooms are nice with decent views but what really makes it a five star place for me is the service and the great staff. Also the bar downstairs has a very laid back vibe which is great for catching up with friends or just relaxing from work.

Where do I start. This will be long but I feel it is necessary.Since I have to give a star I will for Eden who works there, she was nice but what I needed and what I asked for was completely disregarded. My pup is a long haired Havanese a who got poop  and bark all over herself and her butt became matted, I gave her a nice bath and while she was still wet and drying my husband called and said " hey can you take our puppy?" Last minute so I appreciated that. I promptly wrapped up my pup and brought her in, I told 2 or 3 separate people do not shave her. Please do not shave her. Just a trim, and keep length on her. They said ok. I looked at the notes even as they were doing drive up service due to covid19 so I signed the agreement for my car. Then a younger pretty girl with long brown hair came out and said she could help, and I told her don't shave her. Everyone said ok. I remember even saying " I don't care how much this costs as long as you take care of her and don't shave her"

Then I get home, around noon maybe Eden called and said how long do you want her hair? I am like OK ?? ‍well I was super nice about it and sent Eden 3 or 4 photos showing her I would like her hair to still be long. Eden put me on hold for about 5 min to ensure the groomer could do what I had  provided in the photos, she came back and said yup all is good , I again stated please don't shave my pup she's a Havanese so she has longer hair. I said thank you and how excited I was to see the pup all cleaned up. Then I got a call saying I could pick her up at 2. Still never mentioning anything about shaving her. 
I get there, while I am in the car I pay $65.00 then they say " let me get Khalessi " they bring her back. COMPLETELY shaven. Yup. Then the groomer who I never met ( wasn't the younger girl as I thought) it was an older women wearing glasses who introduced herself as the groomer and proceeded to say she was UNHAPPY with the cut, I bring the nice person I am held in my tears and said " wow  you shaved her" she said she was so matted she had no choice / when in fact yes her leg areas may have had a couple knots but I said do not shave my dog 20 times, or more they could have easily called and said sorry we will have to shave her it's the put principle. I still tipped her as I am a good human being. I send a photo to my husband and he says" they still charged you?" Yes they did. After many calls and arguments as to the fact that they never even offered to refund my money back or even a tiny bit for the pure inconvenience.... livid. My husband even called and spoke to Eden and Eden said " yes your right all my notes say don't shave her" ugh.....livid.
Beyond, this is my dog who should not be shaved and again they never even said sorry to me. Never again will I ever go here , my regular groomer the hairy hound on Hercules was too busy to take her and there is a reason why, they are so busy because they are so good. They would have never done something I asked them not to plain and simple.. Oh and I almost forgot. When I picked Khalessi up she handed her to me and said " what breed is she"?! Right then I knew I made the worst decision by going there. I wrote it down, I told them I said it so many times, she's a Havanese so I want her hair to remain somewhat long please. 
Do not go here if you love your dog, do not go here especially with a long haired dog they will lie and say they are matted you only charge you more and shave your dog.....

DUDE!!! I didn't even know about this place until one of the Best Buy employees told me I might have luck getting a GPU there. Low and Freaking behold he had a 3080!!! Literal Goose Bumps! I was finally able to finish my build. He also helped me out with some extension cables and advise on my first build. Next up will be a 1440p gaming monitor that I will definitely be picking up here!

Highly Recommend!!

Shop Local!! I wish I would have known earlier.

*** also, that review from "stabk e" is totally fake. It's his only review, and he's from San Fran???

This location is beautiful. Parking was not bad. They had outdoor seating on the side adjacent to a walking trail.

The food here was just ok. Bread came out cold but looks as if it was oven roasted. I had the egg sandwich. It was kinda bland, on the cold side. 

The grits were good according to my friend. Service was good, seems understaffed during brunch. Because their was only one server for the whole restaurant. 

I will have to come back another time to try out the food and rewrite my review.

Update to previous review: Philter is one of our favorite coffee shops in the area. The people are always welcoming and the atmosphere is cozy. Lately, though, the cappuccinos/lattes we've been ordering have been warm and not hot. :( This has been the case the last 10 times we've visited, but I don't think it had always been that way. We like to relax and read a book while sipping out coffee, but it's hard to enjoy if we don't drink super fast because the coffee turns lukewarm then cold pretty quickly. I know coffee/espresso needs to be a certain temperature when brewing, but I hope Philter might consider cranking the heat up just a little bit :). I really do love Philter, but I also love hot coffee! :-/

We had dinner at Panorama tonight for my friend's birthday. The dining room is nice with a warm feel.  The bar is up front and there are tables in two different dining rooms. The ambiance is sweet...calm with mellow music playing and candles on the table. I appreciated that we could enjoy our meal as well as easy conversation.

We all ordered wine flights and the server left the menu on the table so we could follow which bottle we were drinking from. We all ordered the cab flight and the wine didn't disappoint. 

We started by ordering the fried calamari fritti and beet salad to share. Our server forgot to put the order in for our appetizers but the evening was redeemed when the manager apologized for the over sight and brought our previously forgotten appetizers and said there would be no charge. It was disappointing to not receive our appetizers with our wine, but I appreciated how the over sight was handled. The calamari was fried perfectly and tasted fresh with a broccoli rob pesto. 

My friend and I ordered the duck with goat ricotta polenta, salt-roasted beets, huckleberry mostarda. The duck was cooked very well and the salt-roasted beets added a nice flavor to each bite. My other friend ordered crespelle, lobster & crab filled crepe, lobster sugo, basil hollandaise while the other friend ordered chitarra: clams, lump crab, white wine, parsley. They both were pleased with their meal.

We ended the meal by sharing the tiramasu affagoto budino, soaked in espresso caramel and the limencello cheesecake semifreddo which was a pizzelle sandwich with creamy lemon inside. Both were delicious.

Although our time was spent in the dining room, the bar seemed lovely and the wine selection superb. 

Over all the experience was good. The meal wasn't rushed and we were able to take our time and linger. Our server was very kind and eager to please but dropped the ball a few times. The food was tasty and the atmosphere pleasant.

Coop's is a bar, so you must be at least 21 to enter.  It has bar seating and maybe a dozen or so dining tables.  It's a small area and gets very loud inside. I noticed the volume decreased once someone started playing music from the jukebox.

We had about a 20 min wait at 7:30 on a Tuesday night. I'm told that's not uncommon for weeknights.

The windows/walls/decor could use a cleaning. Finish on benches and tables was a bit worn but they were clean. (Really, this is the only reason for not getting 5 stats. )

It's a full bar so they probably have whatever you're drinking. By far the best drink prices we've found in the Quarter; $3.50-$5 for beers, $5-6 for mixed drinks in plastic cup that you can leave with.  I ordered two for the road when we were done.  :)

We started with a side of greenbeans for an appetizer.  They were cooked perfectly and the bacon was a nice touch. 

I had the cajun fried chicken with jambalaya and coleslaw. The coleslaw was  creamy with a perfect blend of cabbage.  The jambalaya was just the right amount of  moisture, with great flavor; Best I've had so far. The chicken was very good and juicy,  but would have liked a little more cajun spice to it.  That's me though- I like a little spice.  

The Duck quesadilla was a little small (8in) but oh so good.

Just a short walk from anywhere in the French Quarter,  this is certainly a place you've got to try.

Stopped by here today with my brother on one of his whims. There are definitely no places to sit, so calling it a "cafe" is a bit of an over- exaggeration. There really isn't even a takeout menu (in English anyway). And the woman behind the glass doesn't have the greatest knowledge of the English language. However, the list of specials DID have a description of the platter, and prices were pretty damned reasonable. Overall, we paid $13.50 for two entrees and a side dish. And you know what? It was pretty friggin AWESOME! I wish I could identify what the lady fed us, but it had something to do with shrimp, beef, a peanut dip and some fried tofu and boiled egg. Whatever it was it was GOOD. We completely housed it down and had some leftovers for later. Not bad for $13.50.

Flourtown location is great, my stylist was Rachel for a single process blonde.  She is very knowledgeable and gives you a good education on the highlighting/bleaching process and why she uses the techniques she does to save the integrity of your hair.  No sales pressure, just outstanding service.  Great salon, I plan to keep her as my stylist!

Our waitress was super friendly and courteous, rib sliders were mediocre, pecan chicken was good. BUT there was a mouse in the dinning room..... there's really no reason for a restaurant to have mice problems. I'd hate to think they have access to the food

Rachel is amazing! she is an expert in microblading.I was so happy with what she did for my brows and I am looking forward to my touch up.Rachel has the sweetest personality and is very professional takes her time and is precise I love what she can do with the microblading her work shows her passion for what she does.Thank you so much Rachel

I hate to say I'm not too impressed and I love love love bread. But this was a different spin on it. My mom loves them with coffee and I can understand that concept they are a slightly sweet bread. And they smell amazing but the smell is deceiving. But i just dont get the hype especially when I'm paying $2.50 a bun- thats the Oh my! in OMB! I hate to say but I would rather buy a loaf a King's Hawaiian for that price.

Always excellent food and atmosphere! We sat at the upstairs bar with Cindy as our bartender....with a wealth of knowledge about every entree and drink in the place, Cindy made our experience at the Royal House top notch! Highly recommend taking one of the 4 spots at the bar upstairs with Cindy!

I didn't stop by here for the poke like most others, I stopped because of the sushi burrito! It was delish! There were plenty of options. All the ingredients look and tasted fresh. I did a build your own burrito with eel, shrimp tempura some veggies and honey wasabi and eel sauce. All great! We even got our picture on the wall.

So, Wild Garlic Grill has been a favorite of mine since they opened on 1st Ave and Grant.   The food has always been great and wonderful wines.  Tonight though I took a friend to enjoy and early dinner.   We got there and a young lady said that the hostess would be right with us.  It took about 5 minutes before the hostess showed up.  Then we had to wait while they took a phone call for a reservation.   We were seat on the patio.   That was very nice.   Our server came and asked if we wanted something to drink.   We were still deciding.   5 to 7 minutes later he came back to get our order (5:05).   We ordered our food then.   Our drinks came we both got sangria.   It was very tasty.   There was no price on the menu for the sangria.   They were not too busy but there was a steady stream of people coming in.  It took a little more than an hour to get our meal.   Which is Cod and the shrimp rigatoni.   So, none of that should have taken and hour to get there.   The food was good and large portions.   We both got full and had leftovers to take home.   Which is a good thing.   My complaint was the slow service from the hostess to the cooks.   Our server did check on us often so at least we didn't feel to forgotten.   My other complaint is that sangria should never cost $15.00 a glass.   We both had a second class but if we had known the it was $15.00 a glass we could have gotten a nice bottle of wine instead.   Yes, the sangria was delicious but $15.00 a glass???  That just about the cost as our food.   I know that drinking in restaurants and bars is where they make a lot of their money but if you are going to charge $15.00 for sangria then that should have the price on the menu.   Especially since the glasses of wine had their prices down.   I know with Covid and things having to have been shut down and then starting back up slowly has been hard but it has been hard on all of us.   So raising prices is expected but then again we all have lost money and maybe even jobs.   So, if Wild Garlic Grill and other restaurants want to have people to keep coming in maybe they should not raise the prices quite so much.   $2.00 to $3.00 more on each menu item in a bit much.   I am not sure if I will go back because I really have always enjoyed Wild Garlic Grill but with prices being so high and service being slow I may not.   I am glad to see that they still had many patrons  filling up the place. 
H. B.

First impression upon walking in is that the place is huge and they have more TV's than you have ever seen.  Not a bad thing.  Then you try to speak with a hostess to get a table and EVENTUALLY they will acknowledge you but then on my first visit for Monday Night Football I was told that no tables were available.  Okay, that seemed a bit strange given that I saw at least 5-10 four tops that were completely open and only a couple people who appeared to be waiting for tables by the host station but instead we chose to sit at the bar, have a few drinks, and some appetizers.  Even at the bar service was fairly slow but they made an okay drink and finally the food came out after quite a long wait.  Cochon de Lait tacos were actually quite good - after adding salt.  The side dish of Mac & Cheese was also decent - after adding salt.

The space has huge ceilings and lots of wood and TV's as you would expect from an upscale sports bar, plus the outside courtyard including bar seats that are served through open windows is a pretty cool option.  There only appeared to be one large TV outside though so for watching games it's probably not ideal.  In terms of food it appears Manning's does a decent job for a sports bar other than the kitchen having an aversion to salt so only eat here if you're comfortable adding salt to bring out the flavor in whatever you order.

On my first vist Manning's was average or maybe a bit below - it's obviously got a ton of Harrah's money in it so I don't really call this a "locally owned" place despite Archie Manning's involvement.  I'd like to go with 2.5 stars (which Yelp reviews appear to have pegged perfectly) but will round down to 2 and I definitely prefer to spend my money at local places in the future.  However, with the lack of good sports bars in NOLA where you can get a seat and have decent food I may return to Manning's at some point.  I'd like to hope it will be better, but all around there is little indication that much improvement can be expected.

If there was a zero rating I would use it.  Read before ordering!!!  I ordered a wig from "this place" on Friday, 3/20/18.  They charged my card on that date (through Paypal). Usually a company charges you when the item is shipped.  When I didn't receive it by the following Friday, I called to no avail.  I then sent an email in which they replied that they were sorry for the delay and that the wig would be shipped on Monday (4/02/18) and a tracking number sent. When that wasn't done, I called again - no answer.  Then emailed (Tuesday 4/3) at 12.  They replied at 2pm indicating that item is out of stock.  That's it. No documentation of refund/ credit etc.  I called - after about 45 minutes, "Anna" answered and was so rude, it was ridiculous.  She seemed upset that I didn't have a six digit order number.  I see now that I provided her with the PayPal requisition number; but I didn't now that.  When asked if she would take a msg for the manager, owner, she stated "No, you can call back".  It takes an enormous amount of time to get anyone to answer the phone (as this is the 2nd day of trying).  The phone just goes through a series of prompts/ loops.  Anna hung up on me twice and left on hold twice.   And neither time when I called back (still her) did she once say "oh I apologize for getting disconnected". She then put "Morgan" on the phone.  She was initially very nice but insisted that I was being rude to her when I asked her about a refund??? I told her absolutely not, I was trying to determine if I could get a refund - as their email was vague and didn't state one way or the other.  She then said "oh ok" (perhaps she already thought I was going to be nasty?).  She did indicate I could receive a refund (after repeatedly telling her I don't want any other wig or another color of the same wig) and to look for it in 7 to 10 business days.  I will NEVER do business with this company again; EVER.  And I am shocked that PayPal would stand for this type of business.  She tried to have me order another wig.  I politely declined.  I will leave a bad review for this company everywhere possible.

And yes this is the correct company: 1212 Chestnut St.
Philadelphia PA 19107 is the address on PayPal (I've notified them as well; bad business and horrible customer service).  Steer clear from online ordering.

Good food, good service, good price!
I was in town staying at the Sheraton and with Mardi Gras parades clogging everything up, this place was a nice reprieve, just barely off the beaten path without the crowds and long wait time.

I ordered a chicken, fish and shrimp combo. Depends on what you like,  I thought the chicken and fish was the better choice. 

The shrimp was big, but the battered is more doughy. So 1 or 2 was enough. 

The fish used a different battered. It's think and crispy. However, I ordered the steak which I should have ordered the thin sliced one. The fish steak has bones.  

Chicken wing. Loved it. Excellent battered, good taste. Juicy too.  

My experience was a 3 stars, I've stomach issue afterward and I ate fried food all the time.  And the French fries was soggy.  Not cool. But I was so full I couldn't eat the fries anyway.

We had an unexpected layover and the airline provided us a room near the Philly Diner.  We walked over and we were immediately greeted at the door and invited in.   The waitress was very friendly and helpful and the cheesesteak sandwich was delicious!    The service was excellent!   It is worth the walk!
The quality lies in the taste & that's it. Portions are terrible majority of the time, & price is usually higher when you get there to pay. In what world is this a large Stromboli..

Raw, BLOODY chicken. The soup is the only thing that kept this from being a 1 Star review. I have had numerous issues ordering takeout or delivery (UberEats) from this location. I'm not sure why I kept trying again, but this was the last time. The food isn't cheap to begin with, but it's a total waste when you can't eat it at all.

I probably don't go to this place enough since it's right next to my apartment. 

The rum list is both stunningly long and dizzyingly unmanageable. But the key I suppose is to just get a mixed drink, because only pirates drink straight rum.

The mojitos are consistently the best in the city, with some creative choices on the menu. My favorite rum drink has always been the Dark and Stormy, which is only of the cheapest things on the menu and DAMN good. I like it with lemon, but that's just me.

If you're with a bunch of friends you could spring for the $60 flaming volcano drink, which tastes like Hawaiian punch and looks ridiculous.

Brad's rating (out of 5):
Drinks: 5
Price: 3 (isn't rum a cheap mixer?)
Decor: 5 
Service: 4
Wild card: Sent back one of the huge $60 drinks because it had a fly in it. But they replaced it!

I never had a poboy in my life and going here to try my first ever poboy was one of the best decisions my friends and I made on our trip to NOLA! I ordered the fried shrimp poboy, which I halved with my cousin, and it definitely hit the spot! You have the option of ordering a poboy dressed (with the usual mayo, lettuce, pickles, and lettuce) or undressed -- but honestly, why would you not have it dressed? I love the crisp and crunchiness of the poboys and that they did not skimp out on the shrimp (our sandwiches were overflowing with fried shrimp). The poboys on the menu come with a side of creole slaw, fries, or onion rings -- I opted for the slaw, which was regular cole slaw with a little kick to it. 

I also ordered a side of spiced potato salad, which was also really good! For drinks, I ordered the Hurricane. I was disappointed in the Hurricane from Lafitte's and decided to give it another try at Mahony's and the verdict? TASTY and I liked that I did taste the alcohol (as opposed to Lafitte's watered down version). It was a perfect mix of sweetness and booze! 

The interior of Mahony's is very modern-looking. The bar area was impressive, but what really caught my attention was the small area at the very back, which featured Tabasco sauces that spelled out "NOLA." It's a cute background for an IG-worthy photo opp! 

Our waitress Ashley was a GEM. She's the definition of southern hospitality and even recommended places for my friends and I to go to! She was super bubbly and made our experience at Mahony's even better!

Food choices were quite interesting. The spring rolls were fresh, crisp and delicious. The Ramen with Tempura was tasty. The Chicken Sontanghon was quite interesting. The bean thread noodles in it were something new for me. Everything was so fresh feeling. The had at least a couple of decent craft beers to choose from, Daredevil and Bells were tapped at the time. Beer was a bit foamy though...We got brave and had dessert: a warm chocolate cake with raspberries, topped with a dark chocolate ice cream that just absolutely must have come from choco- heaven...Service was fine, friendly and got samples of beer (they were sure which beers they had).They had a good crowd for our late dinner so they seem to be catching on well...I would absolutely recommend the place...the dessert OMG!

Ahh..the Devon's of old has returned and I for one am thankful.  We honestly stopped frequenting after the last fiasco of fish that looked to be taken straight from a Gordon's Fisherman's box. However, they have redeemed themselves after an awesome dinner with a server that was attentive and knowledgeable, offering the just perfect amount of casual conversation and service.

Our food was tasty, hot, and prompt. The server had a working understanding of our wine and offered an excellent assessment of our ordered bottle.  

Welcome back Devon's, we missed you.
The bread pudding is amazingly delicious! We ordered last year for Christmas and it was the best!

Good little sangwich shop with plenty to offer.  Inside is rather small, but cozy.

I ordered the large Greek salad and a #2 (ham/salami) sandwich. Staff was very pleasant and listed all the items that are included in the sandwich, (lettuce, tomatoes, onions, Italian dressing). I opted to keep it the way it came.  

The Greek salad was just ok. It was pre-made, but had all the right amount of ingredients (olives, feta, pepperocinis, etc).  The sandwich was also just ok.  Honestly,  I wasn't a fan of the tomatoes.   Maybe it was the way they were looking at me!  They were very soft and liquidy.  The bread didn't seem fresh at all. Some parts were chewier than others.  I dare say that the sandwiches at a nearby grocery store are better.  Even the pre-made ones.

While we love the bagels, we won't be back. They REPEATEDLY short us when we buy a dozen. I bought 2 dozen and they shorted me 6 bagels. I discovered when I got home. I bought a dozen to send to a friend's house so I took them all out of the bag to re-bag into 2. I guess they figured by the time I got home I would feel like going back. I did go back though. I just brought home a 'dozen' and it was short 2 bagels. Why boast giving a baker's dozen (nobody does that anymore) when you can't even count to 12? What a shame. I don't think it is accidental.

I have to side with Brett on this one. My first encounter with Wright's was at a friend's birthday gathering where I tried a piece of coconut-pineapple cake. The second time was another party with another cake. The most recent time, I finally made it a point to go and get a sandwich and some cake to go.

You go in, stand in a line (or not, as I went on an off-hour), place your order, wait for it, check out, and find a seat in their dining area. Not the most friendly setup, but it works. I ended up getting the New Yorker and wasn't too blown away by any means. Yeah it was a large sandwich, but it felt like some of the meat could have been fresher. I opted to wash the salt down with a mix of sweet and mango teas, and was actually really surprised to see they had a few different options at the drink station. 

I got my slice to go and it was good, as with my other cake experiences. I think it might just be me, but most of the time I scrape some of the icing off as it was just too much sugar. Otherwise it's a pretty tasty treat.

Shady, Misleading, Unethical.  CROOKS!  I went to SB Honda to buy out my lease.  Even though my lease has no provision for any fees at  End of Lease or to exercise the Purchase Option, the finance manager repeatedly told me that Honda Finance REQUIRES a $500 additional payment to buy a vehicle at end of lease.  He swore that it was Honda, not the dealership's requirement and he could not waive or reduce it.  

I signed the sale contract, then took it home to review.  (yeah, I know - review first, then sign)  Not only did they add $500 to the purchase price of the vehicle (instead of putting the fee on a separate line item, but they charged for smog check and smog certificate (which they didn't perform) AND registration and license fees - which I proved I had already paid.

I called Honda Finance and learned that there is no Honda-mandated fee, that it was up to the dealer, but had to be clearly detailed in the contract.

When I brought all this to the attention of the finance manager, he punted to a sales manager, who offered to void the contract.  Which I did.

How many people are being taken advantage of,  unaware of these illegal practices  Their greedy short sightedness, cost them a vehicle sale of a friend I brought with me, and of course, the loss of all my future business.

Go to Oxnard, Thousand Oaks or Woodland Hills, all of whom have treated me better. with the several Hondas I've acquired for myself and friends over the years.

Came to check out their beer selection from what their insta showed. They had one of the ones I wanted the sour berry blast one but didn't have the bomb pop seltzer one I wanted but will come back to grab it. The atmosphere was great so next time I come back I'll sit eat and drink!

This is one of the worst gyms I have ever been to! Never go here! The equipment is amazing and I love the gym setup but the employees do not care about you and treat you horribly. I've had several problems within just one year of this membership.
The food was of below average quality. It tasted to sour and the portions are not worth the money. But will continue to order their sandwiches.

Eh. Not much to talk about. One complain their food sizes are very small. At least for adults. They often mess up the sizes of drinks. But usually they make it bigger and charge you for smaller so it is okay. It can be fun to eat on the go though so that keeps this place at 3 stars. Got to admit they have some tasty food. Their large fry is a Burger King small. At least close to it. But due to tasty food and the fun setting in the car I give it 3. However you due need a lot of room to store your order. In the front you can use the dashboard. In the back just use extra seats. I can say this, eating in the car is better than outside on the tables. One time we tried that and our pile of napkins flew everywhere and we needed to fetch them. Also the birds love to steal food. Or at least try to. I suggest putting a napkin over any food containers to try and keep heat inside. So yeah the car is better.

I loveeee this park. It's so awesome. I took photos here and I always walk here. I just wish people would not litter when there are so many trash cans in that area. I've seen so many different ducks and I saw deer as well which was awesome.

Needed a lot of alterations for my quince dress and she did above and beyond!!! She made a train in the back, fixed the bust, and hemmed the bottom so it wouldn't drag in the front. It was perfect and she did it all for a decent price. Would highly recommend!

This is one of those reviews that will seem inconsistent...I've been here several times. I love the food. I love the atmosphere. I don't find the service warm. The tables are too close together. No matter when we go and even if Every table is empty we get asked if we made a reservation and then there's some hemming and hawing. It just seems unnecessary...there could be a welcome reception for people who walk in when all the tables are empty. 
The popcorn chicken is a siren chicken song that calls us back. The location is so central and the wine selection has been pretty good every time, so we keep going back. 
You can see, there are many reasons to go but go with eyes open to some of the drawbacks mentioned above as well as parking can be iffy. It's all street and paid.

This bloody band aid and wrapper was in my daughter's salad. The management only gave us a refund for our food. Since the band aid had blood we have to follow up with medical care. I asked for an incident report and received nothing. This is unacceptable!

Slow, rude service. The BBQ chicken pizza is terrible. Has what basically amounts to sushi sauce on it. Without that sauce maybe better. Skimpy on toppings. I personally don't see the reason for all the rave reviews.

Sala family dentistry is already an amazing office and team in itself but assistant Heather and Dr. Justin make an even better team. Both of them work as one by knowing what each other needs to do in order to make the patient safe, happy, and healthy. If I ever have a problem I am with no doubt choosing Sala Family Dentistry for my dental needs and hoping that I get Heather and Dr. Justin.

Been going years to Reno and have stayed with the family at Circus Circus and never had a problem til this weekend when we stayed. We stayed in a mini suite and it seem it wasn't properly cleaned. It smelled bad. My son found a pair of scissors in the sofa bed and we found a burned pipe in the trash. The toilet was leaking water on the floor. As much as we paid I would expect higher quality. Definitely don't recommend.

I've been to pistolas a few times and feel ready to review. First off, their nachos are phenomenal. Exactly what expect, a mountain of chips, toppings, cheese, and meat (or meatless options!). Their happy hour is great and their margs leave little to be desired. Great drink selection. Lately with the quarantine I've been ordering takeout and they've been great. The burritos have treated me well as well as the guac. Surprisingly, their wings are great too with a great balance of crispiness and juiciness with a great sauce. Highly recommend and can not wait to try the rest of their menu.

A true 5 star restaurant. They hold nothing back. Service from valet to dessert room was the best I've ever had. Food was phenomenal. Although it appears expensive, the quality and amount you get blows away any close competitor. A must see place. Cannot wait to go back!

My boss turned me onto this small little place you don't want to just pass by! I do believe this month I've eaten there 6-7 times. I always have done carry out. The gentleman at the desk greats you with a smile and also he is the God of Rum Cake!!! He makes the moist delicious cake every night so it is super fresh. With every meal you receive a slice and my only complaint is I want more cake. Customer for life for sure. 

I Have the owners face and name tattooed on my chest LOL !!!!
The food is AMAZING! The lean brisket and Brussels sprouts are the best things on the menu. The vibe is warm and inviting. Make this a must go to place in Nashville!

It was a busy night as usual. Tuesday evening beautiful 80 degree sunny weather. There was a light breeze. Thankfully we had reservations at 730 that I had made just a few hours prior. I was shocked to even see availability at prime dinner time. When we arrived the lobby was packed with people waiting and I thought for sure we'd have to wait. But we actually got seated within 5 minutes of us checking in. We got a perfect spot outside on the edge so nothing was blocking our view. I love the views here. The food is decent. Service was great. The bar was a little slow. I finally got my drink when I was almost finished eating and that was the first thing I ordered. The waitress spilled my drink the first time so I had to wait even longer. I thought the drink should have been comped. It was not. The swordfish and lobster ravioli was good. The swordfish was bland but everything else on my plate was pretty good so I just covered it in franks red hot sauce and ate it with the rest of the dish. Wedge salad was good. The pistachio cheesecake was decent. Very pistachio heavy. The candied pistachios were interesting and good.

Cate Zone is another top tier offering for people who like actual Chinese food in St. Louis. With the recent influx of Chinese students (and their fat tuition dollars) this region was bound to get more developed and refined chinese establishments outside of the usual takeout variety and Cate Zone does not disappoint.

First, a note about the décor. Most Chinese restaurants (even the ones that don't cater to white people) suffer from an inferiority complex that makes them overdo the orientalist tropes for the perceived audience. I call this the pagodas, dragon sweat, and panda shit approach to décor. 

Cate Zone busts out of this mold with a decidedly contemporary look. The walls are plastered with NYC transit decorations. You will be sitting on an IKEA Vilmar chair (get one yourself for the low price of $39). There is a wall decoration with a poem in Mandarin that doesn't even attempt make it understandable for English speakers. It's a nice nod to the roots of the guys who run the place and their confidence in their own identities that they don't try to pander to rank orientalism.

As for the food? It's pretty great. I love the lamb skewers. Perfectly cooked and well marbled chunks of lamb that's grilled and then zapped with a generous coat of salt, ground red pepper, and cumin. A favorite of Northwest Chinese people, their lamb skewers are virtually as good as any you'll get on a streetside grill in China. 

Another favorite is the sweet sour pork. Unlike the takeout stuff that's usually immersed in a congealed mess of cornstarch and red sugar sauce, their take is far lighter with a vinegar based sauce and lightly breaded, pork tenderloin cutlets. It's a lighter and far more crisp (and probably authentic) approach to an American classic. 

Also great on the menu is the hot crisp fish, fried fish fillets that are have been buried under a layer of red pepper and sichuan peppercorns. With alternating flavors of heat and numbness from the generous application of sichuan peppercorn, even people with low tolerance for spicy food will be pounding these down like a champ. Just be careful to not swallow too many of the peppercorns whole or you risk your entire mouth going numb.

Lastly their version of braised pork hock is fantastic. Using the same basic setup as the hot fish (buried in chilies and peppercorns), tender chunks of braised and deboned pork hock get subjected to a blast of heat and an infusion of spicy flavor from the chilies. It's a novel combination of things every Chinese chef has in their kitchen.

I've only scratched the surface of the menu here, with the soups and noodle based dishes left untouched. If you are a real fan of Chinese food you owe it to yourself to give Cate Zone a try.

This place is terrible. Save you money and go the other places on State Street where the staff has more experience.  For $10 I got a dry chicken salad sandwich that fell apart.  Didn't even come with a pickle or napkins.

This was a seriously amazing event. 
My favorite so far this year!
If it wasn't for the free tix from Yelp,
I wouldn't have been able to be here!

This was my first Taste of the Heights
And I was truly blown away. 
The neighborhood and community 
Really make you wanna stay!

The event started off a lil rocky. 
The check in was a lil confusing. 
But it wasn't too much time before
I got a book of tix used for boozing!

I loved the set up of the event 
It was like a cool, local block party!
Just wandering up each street 
And looking at things that are arty!

The bites and sips that I tried
Were all from great local places. 
So many new flavors for my friends and I 
To happily stuff in our faces!

This is my favorite place to buy baby stuff. They have a great selection of Combi safety seats and travel systems. I love the different toys they have available, and the people are super helpful and friendly. I hope this store sticks around.

I went with a group to Alma on Tuesday evening, when they offer half-priced tapas and 2 for 1 on some drinks. The restaurant and bathrooms appeared to be very clean and well-maintained. The food was fantastic! I ordered two tapas, which was equal to a meal. The cheese and vegetables were so fresh, as was the bread. The tomatoes were some of the prettiest and most flavorful I have found in Tampa Bay. The service was good and attentive. Everyone at my table, about 10, loved their food. I can highly recommend the bruschetta, which had garlic toast, juicy yellow and red tomatoes, basil and a balsamic redux. Yum! 

Parking is a little tight in the John's Pass area, but there is a city-run hourly parking lot a city block away that I can recommend. It costs $1.50 for an hour (( needed 2), whereas a nearby private surface lot was $10! I understand the parking deck, which is slightly closer, is $1 per half hour.

Be sure and save some time to walk out to John's Pass beside the restaurant to see the waterway and the beautiful light at sunset.


Check out inspections of your favorite Florida restaurants by the Florida Department of Business and Professional at:

https://www.myfloridalicense.com/wl11.asp?mode=0&SID=&brd=H

I had my nails done at the salon by Von and she was amazing! I highly recommend this salon, and I will definitely come  back once it's time for me to get my nails done again! I had a great experience.

If I could give more stars I would. This place is so charming and owned by the sweetest family. All of their food looks amazing and from what I've tried everything is top notch tasty. I was greeted with a warm hello and an even warmer cinnamon roll!! I love this place I will be back!!!

This is a great way to experience a high-quality VR experience, without having to make a personal investment in the equipment.  With that being said, it makes the cost for a family of 3 ($135/hour), more reasonable than $5k+.

We will definitely be back, but not as soon as we'd like (since the cost is a bit high for our budget.)  There are ways to save, though... we were told if you follow on FB/Instagram (maybe Twitter?), there are occasional offers.  Also, if you return quickly (within a month), they offer a 10% discount off a booking, provided in their follow-up email to your reservation.

Jj the chef is super mice, always introduceses himself and makes complementary tasting. They have most of the usual rolls not too many  combination rolls. They offer Poke never tried it, my boyfriend enjoys their General tsos chicken. My usual is miso soup, gyoza and a spider roll (tempura soft shell crab) . Definitely recommend this for a good sushi spot. They lokk like they have  very good  lunch specials as well!

Staff was extremely friendly, they really went out of their way to make us feel welcome and explain the menu. Fun stop for a low key, guilty pleasure type meal, but probably a little heavy for a regular lunch stop. Surprisingly, we didn't order a hot dog - we shared the pizza calzone, Italian beef, and onion rings. My husband said the Italian beef is better than Portillo's (our Chicago area favorite). Definitely worth checking out!!

I grew up in Northern VA where Korean food is abundant and I ate/still eat a lot of it whenever I'm home. To me, the center city location is just ok. Food is good but not great and the menu is super limited. They do give you a good amount of banchan. I had the dolsot bibimbap recently which was good and the seafood pancake. My friend kept biting on hard pieces from the pancake that the waitress/sous chef told us was cartilage from the squid. I definitely believe them, just have never had that experience with other pajuns before. I think this place does the job in satisfying Korean food cravings in center city since there's a general lack of it but not my favorite place in the greater area.

Went on a pastry investigation and found decent pastries and sweets. Franz's and Backstrub bakeries make more European pastries than Krumblz (IMHO), but the prices and sizes at Krumblz are wonderful. I got a huge croissant for about $1.25, and my friend's Red Velvet cupcake looked good. Her frosting was surprisingly firm, indicating to me the amount of sugar in it. A winning feature of Krumblz is that they claim to make their own pastry dough daily. 

Vegetarians should initially avoid Krumblz. They have only 1 non-meat option for both breakfast and lunch (does grilled cheese sound good?). Hope they upgrade their menu to include some vegetarian options. -1 star for meat bias.

Second and last time coming to Neo.  My boyfriend, mother any myself bought a $60 Groupon 30.  and had $110 bill.  My food was fine, nothing to write home about but pretty good.   Boyfriend had his usual Mongolian beef, it was ok.  The lemon grass soup was awesome!  Moms salmon was ABSOLUTELY FOUL!  It was fishy, very fishy and so terrible.  Ha, sadly we all tried it because its embarrassing to be that guy or that table in this instance so we had to verify mom wasnt being picky or fickle.  She wasnt.  I let our waitress know that everything was great except for the fish.  She apologized and asked if mom wanted anything else instead.  By this time we were completely done eating so mom took the safe route and ordered orange chicken to go.  When the bill came the salmon was still on there and the orange chicken was as well?!?  We were told because we had purchased a groupon the fish could not be taken off of the bill?  What world does this make sense in.  I told them I absolutely refuse to pay for both and about a half and hour later the waitress who was the liaison finally took the salmon off of our ticket.  We were then informed if we came back with a groupon "we wont be allowed to do this again".  What?  Serve us bad fish?  Make us sit stewing for a half an hour?   Or take terrible uneaten fish off of our ticket?   My mom left a note for the manager, explaining what happened.  I think we were all hoping for some sort of apology after being treated like we were trying to rob the place.  Surprise surprise, someone did call!  He told her they had handled the situation correctly, the fish was fine and that people who use Groupons are more demanding and difficult.  I had 30 off of a 100 ticket with my Groupon savings.   This food was not worth a single penny of it at this point.   Neo Malaysian Kitchen, I hope your superbly savoy business sense treats you well.  Maybe you could introduce yourselves to a thing called customer service.  If you do, make sure you grab a hold of it because clearly it escapes you.   P.S.  Calling and arguing with a dissatisfied customer do not create return business.

A pretty nice clean bar, one of the favorites of Brandon.

The food is a little better then your average bar food but it is a fun place to go to drink and hang with friends. It can get very busy and very loud in here on the weekends so expect to be patient with the bartenders and servers trying to keep up. 
We don't come here often because of the crowds, but it is crowded for a reason! When people find a place they had a lot of fun at where they received decent service and didn't pay way too much for drinks, they tend to go back.

$10.00 pitchers of margaritas!

LOVED this place and will definitely be back!

Looking on line....it looked great!  Driving up and seeing it in a strip mall....was totally skeptical.

Enjoying the AMAZING food, sharing small plates, having fun ordering via the iPads...it was a fun dining experience.

Food was wonderful.  Portions were big and prices were very reasonable.  Decor was comfy and totally forgot what it looked like walking up.

Do note, it says "outside dining" on their website...you would not want to do that unless you want to sit at a cramped table out front watching cars whiz by and kiddies exiting the Chuck E Cheese next door!  :)

And it's also fun watching the wait staff balance taking your order and you punching it in the iPad and stuff just showing up.  Loved it.

Quick service and clean place. Staff is accommodating and did a good job with gel and dip nails. Would recommend to friends and would come back again. Also ample parking on the side streets, but bring change for the meter

I would say the good was the location, beer selection, and prices. For Philly standards, the food was "ok," not bad, but nothing special. The servers were just "ok," too. This is good for a quick meet-up, maybe a beer and some wings with friends but once was enough.

When you are asked what you would like on your tacos & are automatically offered beans and rice... I asked could you put that on the side for me.  Rudely, yeah that'll be extra. Then why did you ask me? How hard is it to kindly throw that on a piece of tin foil and move on. Won't be back. The rest of the staff was polite. Just this one guy was ugly.

I had a single enchilada which was not on the menu. It cost just under $4.00. It was good. The red sauce on top was good. Seemed authentic.

The guacamole seemed a bit bitter.  I didnt like it. Maybe the avocados were out of season.

The service was good.

FYI the place looks like it's a motel but don't be fooled by the appearance.
The new menu is wonderful.   I especially enjoyed the Calamari - it was cooked to perfection.

What a fun place to dance in downtown st Petersburg. Great DJ on a Saturday night, they have VIP areas throughout, a great bar and plenty of room to dance. It's atached to the Copper Shaker bar so you can go between the two if you need a break from the club atmosphere. There's a parking garage that's relatively cheap right next to the bar which is a perfect place to park, or any where on the street. Friendly staff and bartenders. It's run by the founders of Cask and Ale. Great place to go for a girls night out. Great drinks as well and nice VIP area. They have been open just over a year at this point and have made quite an impression on the nightlife scene in St. Petersburg. They are only open Friday and Saturday nights from 10pm to 3am, but definitely worth going to.

Fast and good service. Friendly and very efficient. Responded immediately as others never did any follow up. Came right on time and was done pretty darn fast. Cary and his team were professional and cleaned up after their work. Would definitely recommend them.

This is a very affordable valet garage convenient to the FQ. I made a reservation over the phone after trying multiple times to use their app and website (subtracted a star for that). I had an easy time checking in and out, though I will say I think that was guaranteed by the fact that I didn't need my car at all in between those times and I didn't leave valuables inside. Be smart folks!

The staff was really nice that's why they are just getting a 2 stars from me. I was just there yesterday and my nails are already lifting. As u can see in the photos my real nails are expose and have no acrylics. And they hurt bc if it being expose. For a $50 service I was expecting a better job! Btw Tammy did my nails.

Blows me away every time. Everything is just so darn fantastic from the drinks to the mezze plates to the fluffy, piping hot, almost creamy(!??) pita bread that's served fresh out of their wood fired oven. Bless you, Shaya!!!!!!
While this place is in an interesting location, it's a Great place to eat! Not a whole lot to do in the area but Friendly staff and service. Recommend this place.

Came here while I waited for a car service to be finished. I did not expect much because this place is in a mall. Eh -- it was ok.

I got a Rosemary Pedicure, not sure why it is called Rosemary because there was no rosemary. All the products used felt super goopy, the nail technician was very nice.

Anyhow -- probably will not go back, but it was ok for what I needed done.

3 of the last 4 visits have been flawless.  Last night filet was terrible twice.   Salad and rest of food was great.  There was a very annoying man talking and laughing extremely loud talking on his phone on speaker.   The expected response would be for the staff to ask him to go outside.  He was in the bar along the exterior wall.

How about minus stars!
I didn't get a chance to see a doc here
First let me tell you I had my cat before my three children,he was raised like a part of the family. 
I wasn't aware of parking so I had walked two blocks with my terrified 19 yr old dying cat, Who has only been out of the house 2 times his whole life, I was out of breath, disheveled when I walked in & the receptionist looked at me crazy for worrying so much about my cat being frightened on the drive/walk over
The atmosphere was very unwelcoming 
A nurse came out and asked to take him to the back until they had a room ready I responded I didn't want him to leave my sight, she also gave me a funny look and walked away 
While we were waiting for a room my cat was scratching at me to get down, there was a small dog in the waiting room on a leash so I made sure to keep my cat close & cornered in a corner so I could scoop him up at any moment, another lady from the reception area screamed at me "excuse me,you need to keep your cat up off the floor!"
I was really offended at the tone of her voice, i've been to two other vets never having a problem with my cat out of a carrier!
Then the nurse comes out with a carrier and tells me that I need to put him in it!
I explained to her that he has never been in a carrier and he was already terrified I told her I would keep him in my arms she said it was their policy I was not about to put my cat under any more pressure as sick as he was I decided to walk out and go to another vet
I can't speak for the doctors but the people that are working in the front are obviously not animal lovers and are very cold and unfeeling when it comes to someone with a dying pet! I do not recommend this place for that reason.

We absolutely love The Bait House and eat here at least once each time we are in Clearwater. The drunken shrimp appetizer is a must! We love the fresh fish of the day in either the tacos or the quesadillas.

WOW! 2 visits in 3 days, TG for out of town guests. Gives me an excuse to introduce folks to great gelato. These guys do it right. 
****
This was going to be a check-in, but the yelp app said I was too far away to check in. So, what's your point yelp app? Seems to me yelp app,  you're getting a big big for your britches.

The 5 stars are for Frost, NOT the yelp app.
Soooooo good yet so simple I don't understand how they do it!!!!! I got 2 carne asada and 2 pork and with the tomatillo salsa they were utter perfection.
Very kind and quick service today! It was the first time we've used a place like this, and we will definitely be back!

I asked some locals where to eat in New Orleans. I was told that Parkway Bakery and Tavern was the place to go. I was confused at first because I clearly asked where I could get some delicious poor boys, and here I was being directed to a bakery. I was assured that they served poor boys, and a quick look at the website confirmed that. 

After sitting in nearly an hour of traffic coming from Marrero (normally a 17 minute drive, ouch), I came across a huge sign that proclaimed I had arrived at Parkway Bakery and Tavern. There was ample parking in the back. I walked around the building and the vacant house next door to get to the front, and entered through the patio as that seemed to be the main entrance. 

I was unsure whether I should seat myself or order at the counter first. The menu states "tavern full service" and "dining room self service," so I proceeded to the counter. I ordered the golden fried shrimp po' boy. $8.10 for the regular, $11.65 for the large. At 12 inches, the large is twice the size of the regular, so I obviously ordered the large (I'm big on price and stuff... Yeah). I asked for it dressed (lettuce, tomato, pickles, and mayo) but light on the mayo. 

My poor boy came out very quickly, and it was nice and warm. I took a few bites, thinking it was kind of dry, and then I realized there was a small condiment stand where I could douse my poor boy with sauce. I took little cups of creole mustard, honey mustard, horseradish, mayo, and tartar sauce. Ketchup and hot sauce were available on the tables. I liked the mayo and honey mustard on the poor boy. The others were just ok, with the exception of the hot sauce, which I didn't try. 

The shrimp was fried to perfection, and there was a perfect amount of lettuce, tomato, and pickles. The mayo was sparse, but that was my own fault for not knowing better. I ended up eating probably the recommended amount of mayo (or more) anyway. I couldn't finish the entire thing, so now I have a few bites left for a late night snack. 

The decor here is casual and laid back. Paintings, pictures, t-shirts, and assorted knickknacks adorn the walls. The employees are friendly, occasionally coming by to check if everything is alright. There are tables indoors, on the patio, and in the tavern area. Happy hour is from 3-7pm, which I would partake in if not for my 30 minute drive back to Avondale. 

The only complaint I had was that the bread was a little bit tough, so it was hard for me to bite off completely. It got a little messy with me wrestling with the sandwich, causing me to get poor boy on my arm, on the table, etc. I also licked my fingers a lot on account of the sauces. Be sure to keep the napkins close by!

There's significantly better BBQ down the road at the Texas BBQ truck.  Dickie's is to BBQ what Red Lobster is to seafood and that might be giving them too much credit.  Also employees from this place are always near the restaurant smoking which I find gross.

Pretty good selection. I like how this place samples what they sell. The sales are pretty good. I was told by friends that I'd be impressed by the outlet prices. I was not that impressed. I expected more significant sales. The store sales were better than the prices in Wine and Spirits non outlet locations. They had bottles of wine as cheap as $6 and spirits as low as $5.

Wanted to try. Menu looks great. Sit down, wobbly table. 

7pm Friday and they were out of every app. Also out of pork broth, legit the main ingredient in any bowl of ramen I'm going to eat. Hopefully they get it going but they aren't ready to run their business today.
Dark and intimate. Food was amazing, delicious boar, tender lamb with a creamy rissoto.  New daily specials. Highly recommend.  ^.^

We went for our second brunch here in the last few months. I hoped that the first visit was an anomaly. The eggs benedict were somewhat warm, but not hot, and needed some seasoning, but all in all was acceptable. The country potatoes were tasty but barely even warm. Well, we decided to give it another shot this past weekend. It started with a coffee cup that still had the last users lipstick all over it. The eggs benedict were so overcooked they looked like hard boiled eggs. Once again, the potatoes were tasty, but were just barely warm. 

If this were McDonalds, I'd have expected better. But for a higher end restaurant? We were hoping that the visit five months ago was an anomaly, but clearly this place has seen better days.

Service staff was polite and efficient. Management was quite rude however. 

We aren't going to wait for a third strike here. Two strikes and they are out.
Great service, great prices, and AMAZING food! I had the cochon po boy and my date had the alligator sausage and jambalaya! All of it was great!!

If I could give them zero stars for the Worst customer service I would. This establishment is under 2 miles away from my home. I've been a loyal customer for the last 2 years. I just called to order and the man takes my order and then states your too far and I'm too busy. Too busy!?!?! Never again will I order from here. That was beyond rude. Clearly you need better matters to start. I will make sure to have all my family that order from you to never again do so as well.
Amazing theater. I forget how large the cinemas are. Hope to go back again some day.

I have stayed at this hotel a few times and I receive consistency: Clean rooms, quiet accommodations, comfortable beds, and friendly service.

Front desk really showed that they appreciated my business and upgraded me to the business suite. It was a very spacious room that was clean. 

This location is in an industrial area so if you are looking to stay in a hotel close to restaurants, retail, etc, you'll want to stay someplace else as it takes about a 10-15minute drive to get some good food. If you are okay with some run down restaurants they are close by. 

If you don't mind driving a bit then this hotel is good as there is plenty of free parking, WiFi is good, service is friendly, rooms are clean, and I always find it quiet whenever I stay.

Everything I've eaten here has been FIRE! Last weekend we went for my boyfriends moms birthday. We got two bottles of wine for the table, with bruschetta and ahi tuna as an app. Both were so good but next time I want to try the southwest egg rolls because they sound mouthwatering. I got the ribeye steak cooked perfect at medium rare with steak potatoes and creamed greens with butternut squash. My mouth can't stop salivating just writing and thinking about it! Love the pretzel bread they bring, if we ever have left overs we bring it home and make breakfast sandwiches out of them the next morning. We are wine club members and always use our membership to the fullest capacity. Can't wait to eat my
Way through their whole menu. Staff is friendly and knows how to answer any questions. Ask for a sample before settling on a wine.

Well it only took us 2 months but we finally got in. When we came before the wait was over an hour! 

Was it worth the wait? No, not at all. This place is essentially IHOP with a long wait to get in the door, a long wait to get your food and the food is worse than IHOP. It actually makes IHOP look good. I had the croissant breakfast sandwich and my bf had a club sandwich.  I asked for bacon only on my sandwich, what I got was bacon, ham and a random piece of chorizo?! The club was no frills, basic club with cheap flimsy bacon.

The service was mediocre at best. Like I said long waits. We almost just walked out and went somewhere else. Probably should have.

Won't be back. I would rather go to Cracker Barrel any day.

Service and food is still the same. One word, " Excellent"
 That's why I love Fogo. They never disappoint
Tried to eat lunch there today (2/4/12) and they were CLOSED, with a "For Lease" poster in the window!

A solid 3-1/2 stars. We stayed here twice over a two-week period. The first time my wife got the absolutely cheapest room they had which was you basic small room showing some wear & tear, The bed was uncomfortable and I woke up with a backache. The next time we stayed here I made the reservations and forked over an extra ten bucks for a room with a fridge and microwave, which was money well spent as this room was very spacious with vaulted celings, much cleaner and showing much less wear and tear than the cheaper room. The bed was very comfortable. Free Wi-fi and a flat screen TV. Free breakfast. The neighborhood looks somewhat gritty and semi-industrial, but we had no problems and it was quiet. Very close to the 395 freeway.

So please, if by chance anyone else has experienced this woman's brutality to animals, please come forward. This vile woman should never be allowed to treat animals so poorly ever again. I have posted this review on several sites as well as local groups and encourage all of you with similar experiences to do the same. I want everyone to be aware of this beast and to have plenty of warning before they encounter her. Rhonda, I will make sure to share my story with every single person I encounter in this town so everyone knows the kind of person you are that you would treat an innocent animal so poorly. 

I am LIVID right now. I walked in to pick my dogs up (all 3) 2 were done and they looked good, however one of my dogs she was still working on- when I looked through the window on the door, I saw her (Rhonda) VIOLENTLY jerking my dog's head, I am so upset right now. First of all, no one should jerk a dog's head like that, however what makes this even worse is I told this woman this dog had been horribly abused as a puppy and is very skittish as is. She acted like this was no big deal, which bothers me even more. How dare anyone treat a dog like that. And then I look her up on google and this woman has MULTIPLE complaints against her for abuse to animals. I have reported this woman to the humane society and I will be reporting her to Idaho licensing. All I can think is if that's how she treated my dog when I was there, what did my poor dogs go through when I wasn't there??? Shame on me for not properly doing my research. I never would have taken my dogs there had I read these reviews.i keep seeing the image of her jerking my poor dog's head and neck and it's just so upsetting. I had a bad feeling the second I dropped them off and noticed how incredibly abrasive she was, and thought maybe she is more of a dog person than a people person but dog people don't act like that. This woman is disgusting and shame on anyone who knows she does this and turns the other cheek. I have never been so angry in my life and Rhonda, if you're reading this- you are beyond rude, a truly ugly person and why the H would you ever pick a career working with dogs when you clearly don't like them???There is a special place in hell for you and I truly hope you burn in it.

This place is amazing! And our meal got even better because we got served with so much awesomeness from Michelle the server. She connected with us on a professional and personal level and did her job very well!! She was running around taking care of everyone and making sure everyone were satisfied. Again, the food is affordable and taste like a million!! We will definitely come back to this place!

We lived in 522 West Carrillo IVY apartments in Santa Barbara for nearly one year, and we love that apartment. As our plans changed, we had to move out leaving this lovely apartment. Overall our experience at Ivy apartments at Carrillo Street was a pleasant one. We never experienced any security issue, and my car parked on the premises closed to the road was always safe. I left my car unattended for many days at the parking lot when we go out on vacation etc. but never encountered any issue.  Ivy apartments are a gated community and safe to live.  
These apartments are the best affordable apartments available in Santa Barbara. The apartments at Carrillo are located close to UC City College, and within convenient distance to downtown.  
The management is superb. Nirosha Perera and Victoria were pleasant and helpful. They often visited the apartment complex and looked after all requirements of residents. 
During our time in 2018, the apartments were occupied by young people, mostly university students and working gals and guys. The apartments at Carrillo are suitable for couples and young families.
Best service from a Denny's ever. Waitrss Sara, was fabulous, she was so on it made the food just that much better. Food was cooked properly, the order was. Delivered. exactly right too

I've used Old Pueblo Locksmith twice now, once for a rekeying and once to replace a faulty lock.  Both times the service was responsive, knowledgeable and personable.  I don't often need a locksmith, but when I do, I'll call Shawn.

Owner run little boutique of clever chic "must haves". Handmade change and clutch purses with delightful graphics and a few catchy phrases, especially for sassy gals. 
Small gifts for oneself or a friend, buttons, pendants, jewelry. Variety of price points. Always something new. Catcentric...no surprise - she's a feline fancier. Cheeky cards for special occasions. Sweet little treasures like locally made creams and body butters. I adore my Foxy Feet Foot Butter. I've tried a couple deliciously scented body butters as well. My body sucked them up like a thirsty camel. Locally made with love "in the Canadian Prairies". Most of her lotions, potions and accessories ARE locally made, either by the owner herself (clever graphic designer) or local artisans. Her shop has it's own little groove and its in the best location. It was once Sabrina Butterfly's atlier. The good vibes linger.
It's next door to Mandolin Books and across the street from Be-A-Bella in Highlands. This wee shopping block is beginning to gain popularity. Got to check it all out.
Well maintained, beautiful course. Pace is always reasonable. Not recommended for newbies or slow groups.

I have given up on flying in and out of MSY for business and will now be flying in and out of BTR.  Whoever decided that it would be a good idea to have a rental car facility so far from the terminal should be terminated.  A few have mentioned that maybe they will build a new one closer to the new terminal...don't hold your breath.  They built several garages attached to the new terminal...if they were going to move it it would already be done.  The car rental facility didn't really make sense even with the old terminal.  There has to be a story there somewhere.  At any rate, if you plan on renting a car in MSY, tack on an extra hour each way.

I can only speak to the experience of my grandpa in there, but he says the nurses are tough (in a good way) and staff is very friendly. During COVID-19 he tested negative despite some staff and residents testing positive - this tells me they contained the spread. They were good about giving us updates as well.
