When we visited (before the pandemic) they helped us get him ready to go out to eat and regularly took him to his appointments on their bus.

I loved this place! I am in New Orleans for two days and was told I had to check this out. I am so happy I did. The owner was so wonderful and they have everything and anything you could possibly want from a cookbook. I highly recommend checking it out!

This is usually my go to Mexican for lunch since it's really close to Music Row and really cheap. Their queso is my favorite in town (white cheese, very creamy). The guac is okay but not my favorite (usually too heavy on the lime). It's always packed at lunch and people swear by their margaritas. Parking is hell. I love that I can get chicken fajitas with all the fixing though for 6.99. Service is usually good, but it can get pretty slow when their slammed. The only real problem I have is that during lunch the cashier line can get pretty backed up, so make sure you have enough time to make it back to work on time.
Disappointment as the recommended dish was not good and i got attitude when i complained...heard good things but bad experience doubt i will go back

So happy to have a Japanese restaurant in Apollo Beach. We always have friendly and attentive service when we visit. The restaurant is very clean and safe to dine in with the current Covid procedures. They have great lunch specials from 11-3 and dinner is good portions for the price.

Such a beautiful place to just walk and clear your mind, unless kids are smoking and littering right in front of you. I've gone here for a couple of years and over some time it has became a place i go to when feeling stressed. Looking out at the different color sand and leaves in the fall to seeing the city in the distance.

I went this afternoon and they had only a handful of donuts available. Coffee wasn't brewed, and the dining area smelled and felt dirty. A bar stool was broken with a trashbag over it. I heard this was a Nashville landmark so I was highly disappointed.
Beautiful, quaint little restaurant with very unique brunch options and an awesome, welcoming staff. We were made to feel like honored guests, especially by our server, Rachel.

I agree with previous reviewer. I had the chicken/steak/sausage platter - very good! I definitely got my fill for under $15. 
The place is very spacious and bigger than it looks from the outside. They had Univision on TV which added to the atmosphere. 

It isn't on the main drag so you have to know where you are going or happen to be walking down Main St. to find it. Good place to eat and then walk around town.
The Philly cheesesteak sandwich and fries was very good. Great and friendly service.

Best Pizza.  Worst Service.  Had a great time with friends and co-workers despite the poor service.  Stopped by on a week night and the place was packed with a 40 minute wait but took an immediate seat at the counter in the bar area. Small selection of beer and some wine; ordered apps and pizza.  Primary server was great, but when the orders came, the assistant servers wouldn't believe that the order was wrong (gave my pizza to a friend, and took his pizza back).  Couldn't believe she would argue with me about what we ordered.  My friend ate my pizza while they cooked me a second order.  Oh well.  Tasted great, but here is the secret:  ORDER AND EAT THE BREWERY NEXT DOOR THAT HAS A HOT PHONE TO ORDER OFF THE SAME MENU.  More beer, better service.  Win win.

As someone who loves fresh seafood, when i was craving my seafood fix I decided to check this place out. I had been to the one at the beach and I feel that one the fish seemed fresher. Service was good but for the price overall I wasnt really blown away. Possibly the time of year but tasted like frozen fish with not alot of flavor. Was like 100 bucks for two people including tip, with no drinks.

Honest mechanic in Jim. I already was getting my oil changes with them. When my inspection was due I needed tires so I took my car to a tire store and saw they did inspections so to save time thought why not... Dumbest thing. They tried to say I needed brakes, shocks and struts on top of the tires for my less then 5yr old car... It seemed shady so I took it to Jiffy Lube not only did I not need the 1200 dollars shocks and struts but I paid for brakes that the other place didn't do! Jim was so helpful in explaining, Jiffy Lube saved me money and uncovered a fraud "mechanic"! I don't care what specials or discounts I can get anywhere else! It is Jiffy Lube for any services they provide!!!

Really fun spot for the night time for a sweet treat but to continue the night. The drinks were really fun and different. Loved the vibe and overall aesthetic! Pretty quiet when it get empty - wish the music was a little more fun and loud.

Mandarin Hide has an extensive list of delicious craft cocktails. Between me and the hubs we had 4 drinks off the menu. All were well balanced and tasty! Went down quick--haha.

Weekend nights this place is packed. If you actually want to enjoy your drink and a conversation I suggest coming in the early evening. We got a nice seat at the bar and were able to enjoy the cool decor.

Took awhile for anyone to great us let alone take our order after we sat at the bar even though the bar wasn't busy... Probably a good 10 minutes before anyone helped us even though there were two bartenders right by us! I was a bit annoyed and about to give up when finally a third staff member (who apparently was late for her shift) showed up and things went smoothly from there. Still, I expect to at least be nodded at or told someone will be with me soon. Something!

But I got over all that once we finally got some service. The bartender was friendly as he made our drinks and returned again as they were nearing empty. Drinks were great so it was all smooth sailing from there. Worth a visit if you like craft and classic cocktails!
What's not to love. The food. The decor. The plates and cups. The service. The chickpea hummus was fantastic and comes with pita. The rose latte was fabulous.

The quintessential old-school good-old-boy dimly-light insider's club steakhouse.

Nice steaks, great salad bar, and everything else is a la carte so you can have just the experience you wish.

Sperry's is not cheap, but the experience isn't cheap, either.  Everything they do is first class.

If you are a wine lover, you're in the right place.  If you're not, you can still enjoy a great meal and you'll be even happier when the check comes.

They are offering Sunday brunch these days, and the prices at brunch at very reasonable so absolutely check that out - they make a great Eggs Benedict.

Sperry's is locally owned and they are some of the nicest people you'll find anywhere who genuinely give back to their community.

If it's a special occasion, go try them out.  You'll thank me later.

Excellent service. Was seated right away. Waiter, Gabe, was very helpful. Suggested that I go with the bottomless fries option, rather than ordering fries on their own. Checked a few other times during the meal. Very impressed with his service. 
Noticed that he made conversation with other customers; most waiters don't do that.  He actually made suggestions to his guests and helped them decide what to order. 
The only complaint I have is that my sweet potato fries were not very warm. Almost room temp. 
Other than that, food was good, service was excellent. Not to mention that Gabe was very easy on the eyes :)

Defiantly going there again.
Food is delicious and reasonably priced, staff is always nice. They have a variety of toppings for your pizza, and they also offer some good desserts.

The wine was good, but the service was quite lacking. There were a group of young girls in front of us trying to decide what they wanted. They spent about 20 minutes doing so, but not to my surprise I mean how much can a 22year old college student know about wine. 

No one else would move them out of the way so we could order nor did anyone approach us.

When we finally did get a bottle, we sat outside on some cheap long tables lol. The server poured our wine without a cloth napkin holding the bottle.....

Don't waste your money!  They have an automated pay machine but it wouldn't take my bill.  The screen said $7 dollars but it charged me $9!  For $9 dollars they didn't even pre-wash our car off or towel dry it.  My mirrors got pushed in but no one was there to fix them.  I've received much better service for less money.

We have always enjoyed dining with Donnie Scalessa! His gigantic meatballs are the best in town! If you want Italian, this is the place to go to! Everything is fresh and delicious. If you are lucky enough to have any room leftover after eating here, you must try Donnie's Butter Cake. 
Parking is a bit tricky, but you can park at St. Ann's and walk down a block.

Excellent experience! My bridesmaid dress alterations were perfect, and they were completed earlier than expected. The couple times that I called and left a message, I received a call back from the owner very promptly, and scheduling drop-off and pick-up was very quick and easy. Thank you so much for the great service and your expertise!
Craig is awesome and honest!! He saved me over $600 on an A/C repair. If you want honest, high quality, and timely service, see him at Aurora Auto Repair!

Soooo bummed! I was sooo looking forward this having a crepe and we went 3 different days and they were closed?? In the French market. Unless they were somewhere else that we couldn't locate them. It was a bummer for gluten free person who was really looking forward to trying their crepes and had been waiting for months! I kept thinking maybe we were in wrong spot but I asked the locals and they said we were in the right spot!

Very shady and misleading. Would not stand behind work they did less than 12 months ago. Gave me a quote and then added on another problem they caused while working on the car and wanted over $100 more than quoted. The problem mysteriously disappeared when I refused to pay for it. I have given them WAY too many chances! They don't know what they are doing and I won't go back again...I really felt swindled and duped!
Allen was amazing! He gave such great customer service! Also the margaritas were amazing! 20/10 recommend

It's not hard finding someone who wants to take care of our puppy when we go on a trip.  But we also have 2 cockatiels.  Jon Fox from Fetch did an awesome job taking care of Hamish and Arthur.  We loved the notes he left for each day we were gone.  We came home to 2 happy birds.  

(And thank you for watering our calla lily, too, when you saw it was dry - above and beyond!)

I recently moved to town and went to the State street location a few days ago and ordered the Smoke House pizza. That one great; the smoke on the tomatoes and gouda were distinct and paired well with the carmelized onions.

Tonight I was excited to bring my husband but we went to the Park center location due to our hotel location. Oh my what a disappointment; where to start....

There seemed to be 2, maybe three servers. Ours seemed inconvenienced by us and was very rude. It didn't help her coworker at the bar was too busy texting on her phone instead of helping run food and drinks for her. I would be surly too. 

We ordered the Smoke House pizza and it was nothing like the one I had the other night. It tasted as though there was no smoked gouda, the tomatoes were not smoked, and the onions were not carmelized. We ate it bc we were starving and had zero patience for going somewhere else. 

We will be sticking to the State St. location.

I needed to have a classic car smog tested, something I hadn't needed to do for several years. I made a quick search and found this shop. I called at 10:00 on a Saturday morning and was able to make a 10:30 appointment. 

The shop seems great, professional and easy to access. My car needed extending testing, which took a bit of time, but the staff were great and the price seemed perfectly reasonable. 

A great experience with what seems like a well-run, honest business. 

Highly recommended.
I come to Chili's quite often, I love the honey chipotle bbq wings. The service is always  great and so is the food

Excellent southern-style chicken. If you order the hot be ready for the heat! The medium is pretty spicy too. Don't expect a fancy place, not much seating and didn't feel air conditioned. Chicken tenders available on Thursdays. We will go again the next time we're in Nashville.

My boyfriend and I went here for dinner on New Year's Eve. The food was delicious. We ordered the brie cheese platter for an appetizer and deviled eggs. They were hands down the best appetizers I have ever had. Our server recommended the cheese platter based on our entrée choices. I tried to order the special which was filet but sadly, I was told after I ordered that they were out so I settled for the hanger steak option on the menu and my boyfriend got one the specials which was white fish. The entrees were cooked to perfection. We couldn't have asked for a better meal or service. We will definitely be back.

The Hangar is a nice, clean restaurant with a great view of a small airplane runway,              However, looks can be deceiving. My brother and I waited for 25 mins after we were seated before someone came to take our drink orders. We waited another 45 mins for our BLT sandwiches. There are a lot of employees just standing around looking confused. The sandwich wasn't bad, however you can't really mess up a BLT. I really want to like this restaurant but they need to move faster!  If you're in a hurry do not come here!

Been here twice.  My review is an average of both experiences.  Not sure why everyone raves about this place saying it's the best in town.  It only means that this place isn't as bad as all the others.

First visit, 6-1-20:
Met with very friendly staff and my bagel was decent.  Not the greatest, not the worst.  Staff member showed me the assortment of bagels and I chose a salt bagel.  She asked if I wanted it toasted.

Second visit, 6-3-20
Arrived at 10am, started to place my order and the staff member said rudely, "What???!!!"  Apparently, she couldn't hear me but there is a better way to say that instead of how she said it.  I placed my order again, a salt bagel with butter.  There were two gentlemen waiting before me and they were together.  I stepped back to wait and started my stopwatch.  The other two gentlemen got their orders within 4.5 minutes of starting my watch.  I then waited another 5 minutes before my order came out, making it a total of 9.5 minutes.  During that time, only two people placed orders and one of them called ahead.  It was not busy.

My order was called and before I grabbed it, I asked if the bagel was toasted.  She said it was.  I told her that I didn't ask for it toasted.  She slammed the bagel in the garbage can and said she'd make another then closed the window.  She then came to the order window and informed me that that was the last salt bagel and asked if I wanted my money back or something else.  I told her to give me my money back as I didn't want to wait another ten minutes just to get a buttered bagel.  She got an attitude with me and said, "WE TOAST ALL OUR BAGELS HERE!"  I took the money and left.

My experience here was horrendous.  For a business that "prides itself on getting you your fresh food in just a few minutes", it's a flat out lie.  How long does it take to butter a freaking bagel and serve it without an attitude???  No thanks.  I'll go elsewhere, never step foot in here again, and certainly tell my friends of this experience.

Stayed here for the famous Idaho potato marathon. It was the host hotel and I booked through hotels.com and got a cheaper rate than the marathon rate. I have a small dog so when I called to see how much the pet rate was, she said it was only $25 per animal for the entire stay. I've stayed in worse hotels and paid that per night. Driving to the hotel was a little sketchy since the area seemed a little run down. Checking in was easy but the clerk forgot to activate the keys, but both the manager and another clerk bright keys for me to the room. The room was just the king room, and it's the biggest standard room I've been in. I've also worked at hotels for 8 years so I know a thing or two about standard rooms. We were on the first floor and had a little patio that had the grassy knoll and access to the bike path and river. Perfect for my dog to explore. The hotel has a bar and grill that is pretty friendly and brought my dog water and treats. The breakfast buffet was good. They had a guy making omelets right there for you. The park is a mile away on the bike path and downtown boise is a couple miles away. Because of where the room was, one would never know the questionable area it is in. The staff was friendly, the room is huge. Walls are thin so you can hear a lot of banging, and the caulking and shower heads was coming off... And the screen door didn't want to start on the track.. I definitely recommend this place, especially if you have a dog.

I've had the pleasure of eating at three restaurants by the name of Mother's and have deduced that every eatery that chooses this moniker will live up to it. 

I mean, pretty big shoes to fill right? I came expecting hearty, quality grub in a low-key setting and that's exactly what I got. You will get called "darling" or "sweetheart" and you won't be allowed to leave a tip. We came for a late lunch on a weekday to avoid the infamous wait. 

I asked the sweet lady manning (womaning?) the counter for crawfish étouffée with a side of red beans and had it brought it out to me ten minutes later. These ten minutes seemed like forever to me as I drooled over the savory scent of our neighboring diner's gumbo. Ten minutes, and I ate it all in five. AND I was so excited, I didn't take a picture. -hangs head in shame-

To my delight, they really pile on the crawfish in their étouffée. I got at least one or two in every bite. Gotta love them crawdads! The rich seafood stock is not too heavy and does a solid job at bringing all the ingredients together, or "smothering" as they say. 
I never tried savory red beans prior to this and surprisingly liked them as well. I also took a bite of the Jerry's jambalaya that my friend ordered and fell in love with the smoky andouille sausage.

Mother's helped convince me that New Orleans has some of the most delectable eats in this country. My friend told me they've remained a local favorite ever since they opened in 1938. I'm glad that they stayed true to their roots after all these years and appreciate that all of their recipes are online so I can try my hand at simmering that jambalaya! 

Simple, affordable, and all-around good vibes, Mother's is sure to provide you with a wholesome culinary experience.

Great salon! Tiffany and her husband are both amazing nail artists. I always leave with a perfect manicure every time. Her gel mix lasts for 3-3.5 weeks and still looks good! Genuinely nice people and a great relaxing atmosphere!

Paid for ranch, didn't get it 

Pizza looks like it was flipped over and a total mess

We went to this restaurant for lunch with work and did not have the best experience. I think they forgot about us a little bit because we were there for over 2 hours so service was slow. They forgot the water my coworker ordered and also sides that came with our meals. I ordered the business lunch and I got the salmon from the restaurant week special  by mistake which is fine I guess and the waitress brought our sides later once we asked. The salmon was moist but very very salty. Once I got the mashed potatoes they were ok too but the chives were overpowering the taste. The skillet chips were actually the best tasting good we had over our three course meals. The chocolate mouse was ok! Overall maybe this place offers better service for dinner.

I can't believe I've never reviewed 1864--it has been one of my favorite Reno bars for years! We recently took some friends who had never been and it renewed my love for this great spot. The name comes from the year Nevada became a state and al their decor is reminiscent of the late 1800's. All their specialty cocktails get their names from Nevada landmarks and locations and are equally interesting and delicious. My all time favorite is the Amargosa which is tequila based with muddle strawberries and basil. Their drinks are a good price but they don't skip quality. If you've never been, please go!

"Music gives Soul to the Universe,
Wings to the Mind,
Flight to the Imagination..."
                                            Plato

So believes Joel Zazyczny, the founder idealist who created Cafe Soul in Doylestown, PA. Scientist, innovator, philanthropist, Joel operates this simple, yet attractive eatery, as a non-profit to work with the younger people of the community in support of music and STEM education programming and scholarships. For this alone he has my admiration and support; for actually pulling off a well functioning breakfast/lunch haven with good food, he has my loyalty. 

Now fully vaccinated against Covid, I visited Cafe Soul for my first professionally made Brioche French Toast in over a year. Walking in, the space was open, clean and prepared for social separation. I sat at a booth in back where I could see the entire room. Soon, I was approached by the young man running the front end. He was friendly and deferential. I did the short stack FT, and a mug of their Ellis Coffee brew. The joe was fresh and strong as expected from Philadelphia's oldest caffeine roaster (since 1854). 

The frenchie was well panned, with plenty of caramelized edges for melted butter and syrup to accumulate. The egg mix tasted of vanilla and cinnamon, just as I like it. But for the Stuckey containers of corn syrup sweetener, it was a strong reintroduction to a favorite and missed morning meal. If real maple syrup had been an option, I would have jumped at the chance for a near perfect indulgence. 

Otherwise, a wonderful first breakfast out in the world again.

This place is better than your typical Dunkin' Donuts or Manhattan Bagel, but I was kind of expecting a bit more. After several days of walking by Spread, I decided to endure the line that was out the door. I ordered an everything bagel with veggie garlic cream cheese. First of all, the bagels here are huge; I had to take half of it home and this coming from a gal whose family nicknamed her "Bottomless Pit." 

Typically, bagel shops either put too much or too little cream cheese on the bagel, but Spread does it juuuussst riiight, in my opinion. Bonus: you get a strawberry with your bagel if you eat-in. I don't know why this is a bonus, but it is. They also serve brunch and for $8 you can get some bloody mary mix if you BYO vodka. If these are bottomless bloody's, then that's awesome; if not, I'd rather go to a more restauranty place for brunch. 

The staff was very nice, the place is cute and quaint and I'll probably be back to try one of their sandwiches. However, I'll have to wait until my next payday - this place ain't cheap.
I can't put into words the way this company made me feel.  I found a better solution and these people should be ashamed of themselves.
What kind of company tows a elderly person's car, when their are  no signs saying there's no parking? Horrible business, save your time and do not go here.

Good taste... good value... I had the gator bites, Egg Plant pamms.. then toped it off with apple pie... No complaints.. well I take that back.. the Tea sucked.. This time the service was good and the food came out pretty quick.. very surprise consider I have been here before and the food didn't come out for 45mins... it was a little stuffy though.. reason for the four stars.. I will be coming back

The New Orleans Third Wave coffee scene is heating up. The pourover I had here as my first coffee there was only second to Condesa's, my favorite coffee shop in the world. 
An outstanding interior renovation,  from the quality of the LED lighting to the play in contrasts of the light wood and brutalist concrete counter and the floor made of a material I have yet to identify
This is the third store for this Birmingham AL company,  after their home base and Chattanooga TN. Expansion plans are rumored for Atlanta.
Not a large selection of pastries yet but this clearly deserves one of my rare 5 stars reviews,  if only for the complementary shawls provided to cold blooded locals who dislike the cold air put out by the presumably super efficient air conditioning system.

This school was the best thing that ever happened to both of my children. TUSD was a nightmare and once we got our daughter into La Paloma she was so far behind because of the lack of Education she was getting from TUSD it took a full year but we got her back up to where she should have been. Have nothing but great things to say about La Paloma and the staff thank you

First timer for this place and for any waxing adventure. This big girl was greeted promptly, treated with respect, spared a pressure sales pitch and will be a repeat customer. You don't have to look like a freakin supermodel to be pampered here. You deserve it, and so does your partner. Ask for Leia!

Staff was extremely friendly, food was delicious.  Got the Florida Boil and was told it was good for 3.  It would have been perfect for 3, but 2 of us were able to finish it off.  Did not have crawfish, but substituted with extra shrimp.  Only complaint is that the corn was way over cooked and mushy.  Would definitely recommend.
These guys know how to treat customers! Anyone knows how to help for whatever little project you might have.

5 stars for the clam chowder yum! So rich and creamy! 

The fried whole belly clams were yummy, but it was a little oily, especially the ones on the bottom. It would help if they used a paper towel to drain excess oil after the fry.

A little pricey, but better than food court or plane food, so worth it! It was about $7 for the clam chowder mug and $17 market price for the appetizer size clams.  

It is a great spot for a longer layover. They have room to tuck away your carry on beneath you.  

Wait staff was friendly and attentive.  I was so happy they kept bringing the water, in Europe they are less attentive and a lot of places don't have tap. 

Great layover spot!

This place is starting to get better all the time!

 I usually order here at least once a month in the winter and several times a month in the summer. I stopped going here for a while as the service was poor, and the staff not very ambitious.

I had all the usual complaints that a fast food customer usually will make like; never any gravy ready when you want it, request for extra napkins results in no napkins at all, previously cooked foods sadly waiting around in back for any customer to buy it etc.

On the weekend I ordered 2 meals with the usual burgers, fries, gravy and side salad I got the food and it was fresh!  when I arrived home they actually put napkins in the bag as well. 

I hope they have found some new staff to keep the grills hot and the gravy in full supply. It seems like such a no brainer but this location has been unable to be consistent until now! 

I hope they keep up the good work and get some of those customers back into the restaurant. Until this past weekend there were only ever 3 or less customers in the restaurant in the weekend afternoons it is a sad thing to see-such precious real estate wasted because of poor customer service and management. I vote with my money and plan to spend more of it here. Thanks also for an enjoyable AND EDIBLE side salad-its been a while.

Called to see if they have breakfast all day. They do. Yay! Go to order then oy thing I want on the menu- eggs Benedict, a... breakfast item... and they stop serving that particular dish at 2 

Order 2 splits of champagne - the dude brings them and ask if we "want the glasses to go with it"

Traveling through and stopped because of Yelp rating. Absolutely not disappointed. Jaclyn was the ultimate server, polite, attentive, explaining of the menu and efficient. It was lunch time so we split a crab cake appetizer. We had a crab cake at award winning Baltimore Tavern yesterday but have to say this one was better, yes better. The soup and salad was great for the wife and my "Industrial" burger was moist and tasty. Sorry we won't make it back anytime soon.

Great smiling attitudes as soon as I walked in. Very welcoming!   The hallways were a tad cold but if that's the worst of it I'll take it!  Rooms very clean spacious & most importantly quiet.  Free wifi easily accessible and room service was fast & courteous!  I would highly recommend this hotel if you are in the area.

I was really looking forward to coming to this place as the reviews are so strong, but I must admit I was disappointed.

Both my wife and I were expecting much more from the food.

I ordered the chicken pesto sandwich, which came on a burger bun, with rubbery chicken and a huge lump of rubbery cheese with a tiny bit of pesto sauce. The fries were nice, but where can you go wrong with fries.

My wife was also unhappy with her food too, as it came out cold.
At that point we had seen enough so paid up and left.

I hate to give bad reviews, but since we both had bad experiences I had to leave a 2 star.

I cannot praise LunaBella more!  Ashley and Christin (and their team) are simply wonderful!  They have done my hair and make-up for my engagement photos, my wedding, and, most recently, for our first family photos with our 1 y.o. daughter.  They are very professional, while also being very sweet and calming.  

I have never been one to wear tons of make-up, and I am always a little weary of make up artists because I am scared they are going to cake on layers and layers of make up to the point that I am unrecognizable.  Ashley alleviated my fears and uses make up in a way that simply brings out your natural beauty.  I felt like the most beautiful version of myself during some very special occasions because of her.  Plus, my bridal party loved her work, too.  Everyone looked spectacular.  

Christin is equally awesome!  My hair is long, thick and curly.  On all occasions, she managed to make my hair look amazing.  It managed to maintain it's volume and curl, while not looking stiff and dry from too much hair spray.  My mom, on the other hand, has short, thin hair, and Christin did wonders with it.  She is a master of all hair, regardless of volume and texture.

If you want to guarantee the perfect look, I highly recommend you hire LunaBella!

Ok. This business was responsive to my review and I accepted their offer to reimburse my uber fare. They promptly sent me a check. I appreciate their responsiveness, and although I was not able to try their massage services, I feel better about the customer service aspect.
Terrible location. Employees never know how to run gift cards, sometimes they call a manager for instructions, other times they just give up, no pretzels sold.

Pretty interesting location for an ice cream joint and the ice cream is pretty good too.  They have some interesting flavors here and are happy to let you sample taste them.  The price was a bit on the expensive side for the quantity you get.  Parking was a bit of a challenge as this is a very popular area but a few blocks away street parking was eventually discovered.
Nice relaxing coffee shop with unique art work on the walls. Good not great coffee but they offer free refills.

If it was dine in, I would give them  4 stars. Pizza is great, so are the sandwiches, and wings.  However take out orders is when the trouble starts.  No exaggeration, they have made mistakes on half my takeout orders, and one time failed to deliver anything.  Their delivery is very slow, so don't order pasta unless you like it cold and dry.  I still would eat in there, but have given up on takeout.

I've been wanting to try this place and my husband and I finally ordered from them through DoorDash! SO GOOD. The menu is simple and I love that there are different levels to the hot/spicy level. We ordered the sliders and cheese fries! Husband got the hot and I ordered medium heat, which was perfect for me. My spicy loving husband says he wants to try the next level next time. The chicken was so good and juicy! The cheese fries were perfect. We will definitely be returning!

I'm Brazilian and I got disappointed with their food.
I ordered "picanha na chapa" and I need to say the meat was really good, but the size of the sides was ridiculous and the taste was not good. 

I ordered a desert and it was warm (it supposed to be refrigerated). 

It was overpriced as well and they charged more tip than I put on my check ‍

I get the vegan cupcakes and they are out of this world.  But then I tried the vegan cookies and now I can't decide when I go in.  So I get both.

Now I tried the vegan butter and Let me tell you it is the best

Another spin class so I can have more.

The chef and her family make you feel like you are part of the family.

well now here's a story. my dad bought 4 tires for his truck wheel they were in the city anyway we drop his truck off at 8 am and we're told it will be ready bt 930 am. anyway at 930 about to leave the house they call to ask if he wants the white letters in or our.  and I'm like wait are you guys just starting we were told it would be done and are told yea they got behind but the wheels are off and about to put the new ones on. ok so another hour goes by and my dad and I driver over. we don't find his truck in the parking lot or in the shop. so where is it? exactly nobody tells us anything finally 15 minutes later they pull in with my dad's truck and it still has the old tires on it. so at this point it's 11am and they still haven't started after telling my dad it would be done at 930. so my dad being older asks to talk to a manager about why some kid is out joyriding in his truck and why they haven't started on it hours after he was told it would be done and nobody will talk to him. So hopefully someone takes the time to read this and maybe goes elsewhere

Galatoire's is a nice restaurant in the heart of Bourbon street.  It has a smaller dining area than I was expecting, and it wasn't very busy on a Wed evening. Our waiter was knowledgeable and pleasant, but the service wasn't as frequent as it should have been. 

We each started with a cup of seafood gumbo which was rich and full of seafood. It was pleasantly thicker than some N.O. gumbo. Then I had a bistro salad and my companion had the shrimp remoulade.  The salad was adequate for a side salad but tasted a little plain as neither the blue cheese nor dressing had much flavor. The remoulade wasn't spicy but was full of shrimp.

Like most high-end New Orleans restaurants you will have to pay handsomely to leave feeling full. This is a full a la carte restaurant where you pay for the fish, the sauce/topping, and the vegetables separately. I ordered the sautéed trout with burre blanc sauce plus creamed spinach. The trout was a mild fish and the sauce was tasty. My companion had the roasted duck plus broiled tomatoes. While it was a decent sized piece of duck with a sweet sauce, it was served too long out of the oven and was no longer hot.

For dessert we each had sorbet. Overall it was an average meal at an above average price. It wasn't crowded enough to feel this is a happening place, but being on Bourbon street is nice.
Wonderful good, great staff, extensive scotch, whiskey, bourbon list. Try the fries and the pulled pork sandwich. See my check in for more info.

This is my favorite pizza place in Indianapolis.  It is a little hole in the wall place, so don't let looks be deceiving.  I go there every week.  Their lunch deals are awesome as well, $5 for a personal size pizza and a drink.  You cannot beat that!

I had never been to Outback, so needless to say, I was excited and expecting a great time. 
Pros:
Nothing tasted horrible, we were semi-full by the end because we ate off each others plates and ordered appetizers as well. Servers/hosts were nice and the food did not take too long to come out. Not a clean place, but not as dirty as some others.
Cons:
Appetizers: Ordered the Blooming Onion because we knew it was the most popular. I had watched videos of people eating this and it looked amazing and filling. However, once ours came out it was actually laughably tiny and limp. We all looked at each other in disbelief and wondered if we ordered the wrong thing.

Despite the hype, the food was unimpressive and the portions were small.To be fair, I'm assuming every location might be different. Overall, I think I'll stay away unless I randomly find myself in the mood to spend too much of my money on subpar food.

This restaurant was alright. I wouldn't be too eager to go back. I thought the food was a bit overpriced for what it was. The nacho appetizer was actually really good, as were the drinks. But the entrees were a bit underwhelming and the service could have been quicker.

Someone from this Subway called me and left a message after my initial visit and corresponding complaint email. However, I would have preferred to be contacted via email, as I am a busy lady and know that this could have been handled more efficiently via email.

I was not looking for anything for free, but I wanted the owners to know that their product was inferior to other locations' products. I didn't need to have a 30 minute phone conversation after the initial visit in order to accomplish that. I tried to call back and received voicemail. Fantastic! I have no time or patience to play phone tag. It's called email. It's 2015. That's the way most businesses communicate, and how I requested to be contacted in the form I completed to file my complaint with the business to begin with. Needless to say, I won't return to this Subway. It seems no one at the establishment can follow directions or please their customers.
Let me just say THIS PLACE IS WORTH THE HYPE AND WAIT. I would go back to Nashville just for this meal. So delicious and amazing.

Wow. I am never going to KFC/Church's EVER again. Period. Jordan's chicken is amazing. I stopped in this evening to pick up a late "snack" for the family and let me say that what I got for my money was far more than I expected. I ordered four chicken tenders ($4.99) and rather than it being JUST the chicken it came with an order of fries and bread. The tenders were huge! They had to be at least 3/4 of a breast or a full thigh. Definitely cheaper (and MUCH BETTER) than going through the drive-thru for the same for twice as much. My husband ordered 10 wings ($8.99) which weren't the small, paltry wings you usually see as appetizers, no, these were full on chicken wings. They aren't sauced, but are breaded, seasoned, and fried.. and wow are they good. You def. don't need sauce for these! These, too, came with fries and bread. A very good deal. I plan on telling everyone I know about the awesomeness that is Jordan's!

Ok ok ok, this place is under new ownership, and is the hands down best KBBQ place is New Orleans. I loved every moment there, the staff read my mind at every moment. I know the previous owner were not Korean, but this go around is run by the nicest Korean family I've met. They all make a point to make my friends and myself feel like family. The food quality was on par with LA KBBQ. If you are getting KBBQ in Nola, you are doing a disservice to yourself to not come here....oh it's all you can eat too.

I really don't like going to the dentist, but the staff here has always made me feel relaxed and comfortable. They are always very helpful in working with my schedule. I would definitely recommend them to anyone.

Yuck. Cardboard, flavor-less crust with a thin layer of cheese and barely no sauce.  Hubby and kids got it to go.  We were thrilled to have a hot meal after several days of snacky- type food as we were vacationing.  So disappointed.  It was 2 stars for me, but my 9 year old gave it a 4 (BTW, he's crazy picky, likes ramen noodles, Mac n cheese & chicken fingers-- that kind of palette) my  husband gave it a 3, so there you go. Yuck.
This place is FANTASTIC.  Very fresh and a few healthy options to choose from as well.  Staff is friendly and CWE neighborhood is great.  Generous portions, fair pricing, check it out!

If you want BBQ for lunch during the week (not dinner and not on the weekends) Judge's is a great place to go. Excellent lunch buffet lets you try a little bit of everything, greens, chicken, brisket, corn bread casserole, mac and cheese. Very clean place. I guess the only thing that drives me crazy is that you add the BBQ to the meat as opposed to have the meat cooked on it. 

Food: 3/5
Service: 3/5
Location: 4/5

I can't believe I haven't been here before. This place is open for about 6 years! 
The location is perfect. Huge outdoor space on the water. What can be better? Very low key vibes. Good selection of drinks and food. Mainly seafood and not much for GF or vegetarian though. I can defuse myself coming back to just chill with a drink and watch the ocean. With Covid -19 you Joe order on line. Our server was friendly. Food is ok not amazing. I would come back for the atmosphere not so much the food. We ordered beer, mojito( It was not great), pina colada ( was great), grilled oysters snd fish tacos.

Had another fabulous dinner with my wife at N 3rd last night.  We go about once every 2 weeks to once a week.  Always love the atmosphere, the music, the service and of course the delicious food !  Last night we had a delicious bibb salad, the clams with chorizo (which is one of my favs !) and the grilled rib eye steak.  Looking forward to going back soon already !

This place is my favorite pizza haunt in Reno. I make it to this place at least once every time I am in town. The wings are terrific and I am not a fan of wings but these are really good. The Parmesan Garlic French Fries are always hot and crisp and always tempting but the best part are of course the pies. I can't say that I have had all of them but what I have had is great. I've had T-Pane, White Boy, Wrangler and a basic Pepperoni and have never been disappointed. They have a good section of beer and ciders too. This place has never disappointed.

We've been to the Cut Flower Exchange a few times over several years and the experience is always delightful. This weekend we visited to get flowers for for family--the walk-in was very well stocked with gorgeous flowers and it was hard not to buy everything! We wound up coming away with a ludicrous number of flowers for a very reasonable price. As everyone notes the owner is absolutely lovely and kind, which only adds to the experience. Sadly my ambition outstripped my flower-arranging abilities, but the flowers are so gorgeous I'm not sure anyone will notice!

Some of the best tacos in town.
Great prices, wide selection of styles.
A must for anyone who considers themselves a Tucsonan.

My mom is 88 years old but still a feisty lady. She came here to pick up something ordered by another person. It wasn't exactly what she wanted, so we tried to make the best of the situation.

There was a very nice gentleman with dreads who assisted my mother and he was EXTREMELY patient and nice with her, trying to help her out and make her happy despite the fact that the item ordered by another person was not was she wanted (not the fault at all of the store). He really went out of his way. Thank you for doing that, kind sir.

My favorite part of Whole Foods is the buffet. I highly recommend the kale zest salad along with the squash and ribs. It's a great place to grab a quick, tasty lunch. Drinks options include a tap room and a coffee shop.
Felisa helping investors find great rental properties. Felisa has helped find hundreds of investment property for my investors. Give her a call for a free rental evaluation of your next investment

Twice in one week I have lost money at this Kroger.  Last week the cashier keyed in red cherries at a total of over $8 when in fact I bought red grapes that were only $.99/lb.  I did not see this until later in the day because I was unloading my cart at the time she keyed it up.  Then today the bagger says, "There you go!" and pushes my cart away as I finish paying. Little did I see that a bag was missing from my order.  Lost another $8 and change.  I have lost about $16 to this Kroger in a week. Will have to find a better place to shop.

Best wings and roast beef sandwich hands down. We come down from Atlanta a few times a year and go here at least 2 times per visit. You can't come here for the service, but the food doesn't disappoint. If the food isn't quite right they will make it right.

Been meaning to post this for a while, I never write reviews but I got the app just so I could review this place. My friends all raved out how great the food was, etc. Went there on like a Saturday afternoon with my boyfriend, waiter seated us, gave us water and then disappeared. We waited about 30 minutes (mind you, there were two other tables and they were done, but the waiters were ALL talking to those tables and ignoring us) and then 30 after our order, got a Cuban sandwich. Ooo boi that sandwich was just straight salt between two pieces of bread. My boyfriend got a chorizo burger and showed me the patty...I kid you not it was a charred black thing the size of a silver dollar. Then we waited 30 more minutes, had to flag down two waiters to finally ask for the check. Then we waited at the cash register and no one was there either. 

All in all it was the worst dining experience of my life. I don't like ragging on restaurants but c'mon guys. Don't know if we went there on a REALLY off day, but I don't want to go back to test that theory.

This is in response to Jay C's race rant while reviewing The Oz Nightclub.  Why is it Jay C that so many people feel free to speak of and label "white people" with a broad stroke of stereotyping.  I am white and I believe with all my heart that the vast majority of  white people are as accepting of people from all backgrounds as well as their own.  My experience in life also backs up that belief.  I grew up in white/Latino L.A. And white/black St Louis.  I have had non white and non Christian friends my whole life.  My best friend is black, my grandson is 1/4 black, my son has dated two different Asian girls over the past eight years.  "Good" people want race, religion, sexual preference, gender, etc not to be an issue, stumbling block, of life.  I am not the minority of white people, I am the norm.

Service was good. Waiters pretty polite and attentive. Owner was going above and beyond bringing food to cars. 

But French toast was way too eggy. We asked for extra crisp and it was still mushy. 

Also, and absolutely no fault of the restaurant, the sidewalk is a bit narrow and all the imbeciles walking by with no masks made us a bit uncomfortable. So, beware of a slightly stressful brunch.

Tydes Restaurant and Bar located in the historic Coral Casino is a must see when in Santa Barbara. The fact the locale sits right above the ocean makes for one of the most enjoyable experiences. You can see panoramic views of the Pacific Ocean, Channel Islands and the Santa Barbara coastline. While staying at the beautiful Four Seasons Resort the Biltmore this past weekend I was able to partake in the beauty that is the Coral Casino and Tydes. You have to be either a member or a guest of the Four Seasons to enter. 

The sense of exclusivity just heightens the experience as a whole. They say restaurants by the sea tend to have the best seafood and Tydes surely pleased. The calamari had to be the best I've ever had in my life, yes it's true...the best. The tomato gazpacho was simply amazing and the lamb steak was a moment. The menu is seasonal and the food is on point. It's one of those places I will surely make a reappearance at time & time again.
Best sports bar in Indy. Everything on the menu is amazing. The patio is exactly what Indy needs. Love love love this place.

DO NOT waste your time even attempting to come to this shop! Their staff is extremely rude, inconsiderate and could care less about their customers. I had been going to this shop for nearly 2 years, and in the past 6 months their service has been HORRENDOUS. 

I had been going to TIEN, and no matter what, he will have you waiting 30-1 hour past your appointment time to even start on your nails. In my most recent (& LAST) time visiting, I arrived 10 minutes past my appointment time of 5pm due to the terrible Antioch traffic. At 5:45 when he was finally done with the client he had been working on, he decides to take another client over me because I was 10 mins late and refused to give me a time estimate as to when he would he would do my nails. The time before that, I had an appointment at the same time and he took another client over me again, claiming my appointment was an hour later than I scheduled it for. Once he finally did start my nails, he was very short with me and ridiculously rude. And I only started going to TIEN, because another worker AMBER literally yelled at me because I said I did not like my full set she started gluing on, which she was clearly rushing through and ignoring what I had asked for. 

It's very clear that the staff at Lavender doesn't care about their clients, not even those who've been loyal getting serviced there for a long time. I've given them chances despite all the other negative reviews, but I can't keep giving my money to this rude, short tempered, inconsiderate staff and their over priced establishment.
Phenomenal environment! The shrimp po boy was amazing! Sampler platter had a great variety! Food was excellent!!!

The building itself is very nice... all brick, very impressive and at first, I assumed it was an expensive, high end restaurant. I had never heard the name before so we did a quick google search from the car and saw that the menu was reasonably priced and just what we had in mind for a late Sunday dinner. 

It was busy but not overly crowded and we were seated right away. There were many entrees in the $12 to $20 range and they had all the normal Italian dishes and then some. I enjoyed the capellini with meat sauce and found it favorable to other places I've had the same dish. The bread and olive oil was good and the salad was about average. 

The service was very good with a very friendly but not overly friendly server. Her timing was very good and I noticed at least once that she was off in the distance, watching her tables ready to handle any need that came up. 

Not counting two glasses of wine at appx $7 each, the check would have been $36. Not too bad and about what I expected for this kind of place. I thought it was a good balance of quality and price. 

It does seem this place is in direct competition with Bertucci's which is in the same shopping plaza. It will be interesting to see how that works out.

This place doesn't look like much, but it's a hidden gem compared to what's around it. Not much to look at in search of restraints close by, so it's no wonder why it was busy before noon. I ordered the vegetarian pho (small) and the portion was more like a large. It's not noisy, and the service is friendly. However, my pho noodles were in one big clump and hard to break apart. The taste was good, but the noodles refused to break apart. Also, there is no tofu pho option which is my go to when ordering pho. . I was a bit disappointed about that, but overall it's a good place if you're craving pho.
Sent an email to heretohelp@tsicubs.com and no one it back to me except the GM who I had already addressed my concerns with.
Simply exquisite!!! I would def be back to try other items on the menu! The food is excellent and so is the service!
Best Mexican food in STL and I live near Cherokee street where there are many great Mexican places, but this one is even better than all of them!  Also staff is very friendly and service is great!

This is my family's​ favorite Chinese restaurant. I like that I can order dinner for under $50 for a family of 7 and have a good variety. Our go-to choices are Mongolian Beef, Mushroom Chicken, Combo Chowmein and Kung Pao Chicken. They are fast and very polite.
Not a huge fan, wished they had a better cider selection. Wine was warmed, tasted like boiling lava. I dig the live music

Best Pizza in D-Town hand down.

Owner is present and staff is always friendly.  

Highly recommend stopping in and having their wood fired pizza and salad.
Really cheap food and pretty decent quality.  I ate the breakfast special.  Two eggs, bacon, sausage, home fries, and toast.  Enough said.

Even though the food was fantastic, the experience with the lady taking our order was so offputting, that it ruined the rest of the night last night. She was rude and very unhelpful when asking her what things on the menu were. She just seemed like she didn't want to be bothered. Mind you, we were ordering 5 pizzas so it wasn't like we were not getting a sizable order. But the pizzas were good, i just can't give it 5 stars with her attitude

One of the worst dining experiences I've had in a long time. I've been to Scott and Co many times for drinks and love it, so when my fiancé and I decided to have a special night out we figured this would be a place to try. Wrong. To start, the lifting and ambience is way less classy. We sat in a booth that felt like it couldn't decide if it was retro or trashy. They had hardly any vegetarian options and we decided on soup and the kale salad but put server was not smart enough to know those two things go together so by the time we finished our soup they salad wasn't out yet. The soup was fine but the kale salad is truly awful- I wish I'd sent it back. It was mayo on some wilted kale. Gross. Please save yourself some trouble and don't bother with the restaurant just get a great drink at the bar.

I absolutely LOVE where I live. Any issues, there were few, were addressed promptly. Everyone is friendly & helpful. I wish they accepted auto payments at no charge, but I can admit the fee is nominal, albeit annoying. Lol I don't plan on moving any time soon if things continue to be as nice as they are. I DEFINITELY recommend Point at West End!

We needed a energetic dog Runner for are 5 year old Lab and since my husband and I work all day, we decided to call upon The Pets Pal for there dog walking services in Santa Barbara. Actually we called a few different dog walking companies and The Pets Pal was the only service that would run with your dog for exercise instead of just walking. Our lab immediately took to Becky, we started using their service right away! We are so thrilled to have found this service and our lab is too!! Oh and they just started using this program that allows you to book online, track your dogs walks, where, when and how long the run went with GPS coordinates. 
Becky inputs pictures and messages daily and we can see how the exercise went that day. The Pets Pal is fantastic Thank you Sunny and Becky for taking such good care of our baby!

I've had better hot dogs for less money at Sonic. The wait took forever and the hot dog was really greasy. The cheese fries were just French fries and a cup of processed cheese. I always get really upset when I waste my money on bad food. I did not go home happy at all.
I had ordered 2 orders of Peking duck. When I got home I found out that They squid soup I tried to take a bite but it made me sick I was told that they no longer serve Peking Duck
CT provided delicious, thoughful and creative dishes. Every plate contained multiple flavors and textures. His presentations were simply beautiful. CT is a true pro. I would recommend him to anyone.

Literally around the corner from my place, so high marks for convenience. Great pepperoni and cheese stromboli and mozz sticks.  I think the pizza is decent but my boyfriend doesn't care much for it.  Always a clean storefront and nicely greeted.

It was an amazing place! Out of nowhere but has great po boy sandwich! We tried shrimp and catfish. We actually came here for Yaka mein and it was not that impressive, but the king crab was good, and we really enjoyed the sandwich.

I went to Pat Roig after finding him on Elayne Angels website, He is great! The shop is kind of hidden, its a small shop but very nice with lots of new orleans charm. When I walked in I got a warm greeting from Pat. I wanted my VCH pierced, I'm a piercer myself and have seen so many botched genital piercings its scary. Elayne Angel trained and worked with Pat at her "Rings of Desire" studio so I knew he was a good choice. Anyway through the whole procedure Pat was very friendly and professional, he has a great bedside manner- I was very nervous! He shared a couple funny stories with me too. He's very quick and gentle. His tray was set up correctly, everything rested on the open instrument bags to ensure nothing was contaminated, the piercing room was clean and well lit, He layed down a dental bib so my bare skin wasnt resting on the table, He explained everything to me before he did it and why- everything was right. The piercing is perfectly placed and it healed quickly, I was suprized at how reasonably priced it was! I have nothing negative to say about my experience, Pat is truly a master!

I come here for the drinks and the atmosphere.

I really enjoy the jalapeno margarita, and this is coming from someone who does not usually order margaritas.  The endless chips + salsa is a must for every meal.

I also enjoy their brunch options.

I meet one of dear friends from the NEast here for happy hour at least once a month.

Diet? I'd rather have tacos!

My family has relocated to the south side, so I'm always on the hunt for a good place to meet and try new things with them. My cousin was on the prowl for Mexican and neither of us had tried this place so we thought we'd give it a spin! Of course we got margaritas because...come on, it's a Mexican restaurant! And though a bit sweet, they were the perfect Friday evening wind down drink. I got the arroz con pollo (my Mexican go to!) and it was cooked to perfection! 

This place is bigger than it looks so bring the crew, there's plenty of space!

This not so hidden gem of Nashville embodies all that's you'd hope for in a Southern dining experience. The decor and atmosphere is homey and cozy, matching the family style experience at a communal table (for a flat rate per person, you enjoy a dozen or so dishes to your belly's content). 

Pro tip: while they do not serve alcohol, you can bring your own booze for a very modest corkage fee (depends on what type of alcohol, but around $5). There is a liquor store about five minute walk from the restaurant.

The whole meal was delicious, but my favorites were:
-Coleslaw: I usually don't enjoy this, but the lightness/thinness was refreshing and delicious 
- Biscuits and gravy : amazing.
- Fried Chicken: the fry was great, though could have been spiced in my opinion 
-meatloaf- tasty but should be cut in smaller portions to avoid waste 
-Mac and cheese -runny cheese sauce just how I like, and cute roundish noodles that were fun to eat 

Could be improved: 
- mashed potatoes could have been creamier, they tasted a bit like instant potatoes to me
- sweet tea was too sweet for me but good when mixed with lemonade. Would have appreciated an unsweetened option
- should be a couple more bottles of hot sauce for the table, it was annoying to keep having to pass the hot sauce back and forth during my meal 

We went for lunch service but I heard breakfast is great too. A good reason to go back!

These people can't get an order right to save their lives!  
I am lactose intolerant, so I get my morning chi tea with soy milk.  I also like it without water, because a watered-down chi is just gross!  So, what have I gotten the past 3 times I've ordered??. A chi latte made with regular milk, and watered down!
I can't understand how the person taking my order can read it back to me and it's correct, but when I get the drink I have to throw it out because it will make me sick (the milk), and it tastes like water.
I stopped going to Starbucks all together now.  I'll give my business to a locally-owned coffee shop instead.

Recently hosted a party (organizational get together)
After negotiating a price and confirming NO REPLENISHMENTS, but an adequate portion for each person present, we DID NOT get what we contracted for!
The salad was skimpy, the bruchessta good but enough for ONE piece per person, the pasta good but again a tablespoon full and the fish portion was not even enough for a 1/4 of a piece per person. (in all fairness-we did WAIT for more fish to come)
The ice-cream dessert was PLENTIFUL with a DRIZZEL  of chocolate sauce

The to make matters worse, the bill came with a 20% event fee attached!  This was NEVER NEVER mentioned. It was on the contract but who looked after TALKING to the manager often! She NEVER mentioned it!

Come on Maggianno's- This was abominable and I will NOT return as should no one else who wants to have a casual get together!  GO to the reading terminal and be treated fairly!!

Ok, this is a chain restaurant however after dining at a couple locations, this location exceeded my expectations. We went on this past Tuesday around 4pm and dined inside - I hate that I can't recall our server's name but he did an awesome job. The menu was way more expansive than the last time I dined at a Bahama Breeze in Raleigh, NC about 10 years ago (haha). They even had goat and oxtail which is truly "Caribbean". Not going to lie, we were there more for the alcohol because it was close to our hotel - BUT the drinks were fantastic. I had a drink with rum, creamy coconut and freshly ground nutmeg (SAY WHAAA?!) So delicious. My husband was impressed with his rum flight - great rum choices for the flight! To eat my husband got a bowl with mahi mahi, shrimp, lemongrass something...ok I don't remember the name but he liked it. I got a burger (how boring)...but the bbq bacon cheddar burger was yummy!!! And the fries flavorful. For dessert we asked for surprise shots from the bartender and we got the most delicious pineapple upside down cake shots (I think.....) YUM!

Great experience, I was running late(really) late. And I was in a rush. The young lady by the name of Shanique was a great help, her smile and awesome personality had me in a vehicle exactly 8mins of me waking in the door.
I knew they were closing in a few mins of my arrival but her pleasant attitude had me walking out of Enterprise happy and saying wow GREAT CUSTOMER SERVICE. Instead of 5 stars , Ill give this young lady 10 stars.

I took my husband to Dolsot House for a Father's Day dinner and it was great!  It was very busy but, we were seated quickly! We ordered the kimchee pancake appetizer as well as the soy glazed chicken wings! The chicken wings are AMAZING!!!!!!!!! I give them a 10! Perfectly cooked; very crispy on the outside moist and delicious on the inside! We also ordered the spicy pork, chicken bulgogi and kimchee jigae (soup)! The chicken bulgogi was very good the spicy pork was very oily more so than I prefer. The kimchee soup was very pleasing and had such a great flavorful broth! I loved it! We also received all the sides you expect to receive. I wish they included a few more of my favorites such as a radish kimchee, candied potatoes and spinach would have made it all the more satisfying! All in all worth the stop!
Not the cheapest place but pretty good prices . Home Depot in goleta is cheaper . Alot of different stuff so kinda of cool to walk around

My husband and I had brunch here on Easter Sunday and the food and the service were great.  Last week we decided to order takeout and have the lamb burgers.  Huge mistake!!  The first sign should have been when the young lady who answered the phone placed me on hold and never came back to get my order.  I called back and asked for the manager.  After explaining to him what happened he apologized took my order and said it would be ready in 15 minutes.  My husband arrived approximately 20 minutes later.  Our food wasn't ready...small inconvenience except there seemed to be some confusion around where the order was and why it wasn't in the empty bag sitting on the counter.

Fast forward to opening the food at home and discovering 2 overcooked, dried out lamb burgers.  I called the manager who at first tried to explain to me the texture of ground lamb (I've had great lamb burgers at several different places and also make my own).  He later said he would reimburse us for the food. Needless to say we are still waiting.

Will not be frequenting this establishment again!

Now that's something you don't see everyday. A giant, full-scale replica of a Greek temple built from what appears to be concrete and stone right smack in the middle of the city. Like, literally across the street from the hospital. Really strange. But once you get past the weirdness, it's actually kind of cool. We didn't get a chance to go inside, but we did spend a few minutes just walking around the place. Great place for a photo or two, but don't be fooled by the pictures you see online--this place is not as secluded as you'd think, and it's really busy in the afternoon. Guess we don't have to visit Athens now.

It has now been twice where I have called in the attempt to place in order to go & told no go.  This evening I called around 8:42 and was put on hold. Hours posted say they close at 9pm. After a long hold, I was told that they lock the door at nine, start shutting down the sushi bar at 8:45. So I was out of luck. So great that with so many outstanding sushi & other good restaurants nearby they feel okay with turning away customers. I will never dine there or order carry out from Wasabi ever again. Horrible customer experience!

this is by far the worst place to eat in Lansdale. we have gone twice and each time was horrible. the last time, I went with my parents on a Friday night. they seated us upstairs with a large party of people drinking and talking very loudly. the noise was deafening and we couldn't even hear each other talk. we ordered three appetizers: the calamari, the Reuben spring roll, and some kind of egg thing that my dad wanted. the egg and calamari were good, but the spring roll was cold inside, so we sent it back for a new one. when the new one came out, it was literally still frozen inside! we demanded to see the manager, who insisted that she would take it off of our bill.

I got the fish and chips and my parents split a boxty, both of which weren't too bad. when the check came, the spring roll was still on there! my dad insisted on seeing the manager again and she told him that she hadn't had time to take care of it yet. she took it off, we paid the too-pricey bill, and we left.

horrible service, okay food, excessive prices. don't eat here.

an amazing spot, and also very fair pricing!! the decor is beautiful and makes for a lovely meal experience.
the bread is wonderful as well as our entrees, the rigatoni vodka and the chicken vesuvio! every entree comes with a soup or salad, which is a bonus.
for dessert definitely grab coffees as well as the chocolate cream puffs. a wonderful date night experience.

My fiance and I came here for a birthday dinner. The only time we could get was 5pm.  

We started with the rabbit pasta (I forget the fancy name) which my fiance thought was ok and I thought it was great.  She thought the sauce hid the flavor of the rabbit.  I loved it. 

For dinner, we had the special, Branzino fish, and we both agreed it was outstanding. It came in a great sauce with tomatoes and olives.  Delish.  

Service was good. 

Definitely will come back.

We love the place. Decor is homey and the smell is delicious. Service is outstanding and super friendly. Parking is on the street. Child friendly. Definitely going back for their pizza!

Food:

Bread - is absolutely one of the most delicious/fresh bread I ever had in an Italian restaurant

Risotto ball - outstanding! Very rich and moist. Love the flavor and the texture 

Chitarra and clam white wine sauce - very good and strong citrusy flavor. Definitely recommend 

Pistachio ravioli - very exotic. Nice Flavors if you really like pistachio.

Went tonight for parmesean baked shrimp.....was very bland. Tried their polenta....was covered in sauce....more sauce than polenta and the olives were awful....had to pick them out.  Will not be back soon....

I've eaten there many times over the years.  The setting while in a strip mall at first lacks curb appeal, but once inside the decor is lovely, crisp, clean, and authentic.  The staff is very friendly and very competent.  It's a byob.  So, the wines always good and at the right price ;). 
The menu is large and very tasty and, btw, healthy. Food is very well prepared, presented well, and hot!
Prices are very fair.  
I have to say, that this restaurant started off very good and gas only gotten better!  My advice make a reservation, it gets busy!

Dont trust this place for anything. Im a disabled veteran and they took advantage of me 100% i paid for them to repack new seals in the wheel bearings and upon inspection at another repair shop it was not done.  What a joke. The manager told me to f off when i asked for.a refund.  See ya in court small claims for 700 bucks

Omg this is a awesome sushi restaurant that just opened in Mt. Juliet on Hwy 70. We have found one problem. The last 3 times we went in the service was awful. Tonight we decided to set at the bar hoping for better service. Went in and only had 3 customers in setting at tables and the bartender handed us our menu and walked off for 10 min. Never ask for our drinks or nothing. Got out and started talking to the customers which wasn't even her customers. Again this is an amazing sushi restaurant just need new wait staff. We walked out and came to corner pub which got us drinks and food within 15 min.

Stopped in here on a recommendation. New owners as of a few months ago from what I understand. Very cozy quiet neighborhood bar & grill. Beer is cold & a great price, the food was way better than expected. The cook knows his stuff.
Visiting Santa Barbara and needed a watch battery.  This place fixed it on the spot for less than 7 dollars.  Need I say more.

Just had a massage with Stephanie. She is amazing! I've had massages before but nothing like hers. Honestly I was a little skeptical because this is a chain but I am not disappointed at all. She took out knots I never knew I even had and she made it feel good while doing it! Usually when my knots are taken out because I'm so hard on my body it hurts and I throw up afterwards. It wasn't painful at all but she definitely knows how to be rough and apply pressure when needed. The only regret I have is not having a longer massage with her! Immediately after working on my neck tension and inflammation, I could breathe better. I can't wait to go back to her and next time I'll bring someone with me! Her hands are miracle workers and her voice is very soothing. Thanks steph for such a great experience! I scored on finding her!

I like their patio - it's a great spot to bring your dog on a cool night.  You can watch volleyball up close and personal.  We had great service when we sat at the bar and outside - plus cheap drinks!

Wow! Did not expect this to be so good. We found this gem on a cross country trip and now wish we could drive through Nashville more often. The staff was amazing, great menu and they captured the essence of southern foods while staying true to their plant-based roots. I felt like I was at a southern bbq with all the fixins. Tried the Cole slaw, baked beans (incredible), fried chicken. The green beans alone are worth a trip!

We need more places like this!! Come to DC, Southern V!

Simply the best! They are honest and helpful. They did some work on my car before a long trip to make sure it was in good shape. They also called me while They were working on it to ask if I want to get some things done on my own for cheaper of if they should go ahead and do it. The best customer service around and the car came back in great shape. I have never had an issue with any car they have worked on.

Food was delicious. A bit of a queue at 7pm, we went for drinks across the street and they texted when the table was ready. Started with a sazerac and old fashioned at the bar, then retired to the balcony. I had the half duck with asparagus, my partner had the beef medallions rare, a carafe of wine, and bread pudding. Food quality and temperature were spot on. Meat was tender. Nice views from the balcony.
Outside bar, great food across the street from beach! Live music too!! Gotta try the fish and chips!!!
Great prime rib. Came here on a Saturday night and it was busy, but not uncomfortable. I had great service. Sat in the bar and they have big TVs to watch. Food was great!

Had 11:15pm reservation...   got there at 10:45 to be told they close at 11.   BS.     A show had just ended. Why on earth do you close on a Saturday night before a concert let's out? Also, when asked to talk to the manager, I was told I was. Then, when I said well why weren't we contacted if you had no intention of honoring the reservation, I was met with a blank stare. Who are these managers????We are from DC and made the reservation months ago.    This says so much about why you can't build up this city.

An awesome place in the shadows of the big casinos.  We had business downtown and got out late.  Not being from Reno, we circled around and found the Golden Flower by sheer luck.  We happened in keeping our fingers crossed they were not getting ready to close.  We found the restaurant alive, and apparently this place is known for staying open late!  The food was fansastic...not even sure I can remember exactly what we ate, we were so hungry.  Two large bowls of goodness (Beef soup, now I remember).  Very tasty!  But we ordered too much - not knowing the drill.  I watched others who had the routine down.  One of the standard sized bowls (large enough), a side of rice or noddles, and a few beers is just right for two adults.  I am going back next time I'm in Reno...want to try the Hot and Sour soup this time.

This chicken is extraordinarily good. Hot and juice with a special season that satisfies your hunger. Because of the virus they are taking orders at the door. Yet they make it happen with kindness and in a timely fashion. They are wearing protective gear & gloves. Oh and a smile. The Mac and cheese is so good. I give it 5 stars.

I have been to Carmel many, many times over the last few years. It has a unique tapas style menu with unique flavors. Some of our favorites are the chick pea fries, the mini mezza platter, the tomato basil flat bread and the empanadas. We are partial to mostly the appetizers as we are frequent happy hour visitors. They have $5 martinis, cocktails and glasses of wine. Their happy hour apps are great also. They have a nice outside sitting area and if we sit inside it is usually on the sofas. Overall, just a nice place to frequent with good prices and great food and drink. The two of us get out of there with 4 apps and 4 drinks for under $50!

Have no idea why everyone loves this place. Yes, it has quite a list of beers. Yes, it some modern appeal to it. Food, however, is nothing to write home about. We've got 2 most expensive items on the menu, grouper sandwich and grouper pan seared and it was barely eatable, way too oversalted and overspiced. Skip it, honestly. A lot of other places around.
Even though I rarely eat turkey, the "Bobbie" is one of my favorites.  I was thrilled to discover that they recently opened a location in Beverly Hills, CA, a Los Angeles is my second home.

If I could give zero stars I would. I walk in and no one helped or greeted me which set the tone. They sat us at a table and gave us an extra seat that was next to the trash and the bus pan. I had called ahead if this was not a place to accommodate large parties they should have said it. They forgot our cheese board. Two of us ordered the brisket sandwich and it was disgusting. Either the meat had gone bad or it was something other than brisket. Never again will I go to this place

So much fun!

Perfect for group outings. Plus it's right next to a bunch of restaurants and bars.
Oh, so lucky to have found this spot!  It's our favorite Sunday brunch hangout.  Great food and drinks
Amazing! Delicious! I felt like my grandma came over & fixed me the best meal ever!! Do not pass this place up!

Very disgusted with this office. They refused to provide ANY accessibility options for Deaf/Hard of Hearing people. I dropped off a friend for surgery, and was not allowed inside. This is understandable. 

They refused to start his surgery until we provided them with a phone number where I could be CALLED. 

After 20 minutes of explaining the issue, they told me that I must sit outside, in my car, where they could see it, in order to start his surgery. 

They then made him wait an additional hour, while they mocked the Deaf and Hard of Hearing. 

Absolutely despicable people.

They're alright, little too expensive for what you get. Yea they're pretty big portions but theres hardly any taste! But The reason Why I wanted to leave a review was because the lettuce in one of the salads was going BAD! The icing on the cake was finding black spots on my spaghetti in my spaghetti bolognese! On multiple pieces! THIS MEANS THE OWNER LET THEM COOK THE PASTA AND LETS IT SIT OUT UNTIL SOMEONE ORDERS IT!! Never ordering pasta from here again!
Don't bother. Got a cannoli pie that tasted nothing like a cannoli. The crust was still raw.

Mussels are as good as any in the city. The Seafood Gumbo was homemade good. The filet was done perfect. When you go you have to ask for Ana. She is so funny and brings a great family feeling to table. Enjoy
Good place to hang out, lots of stores to explore. The architecture is nice, and plenty of sitting areas while walking around.

Went here for dessert after dinner in Lambertville. 

This place is great. They have lots of flavors to try that are different from regular ice cream stores. We ordered a peach and a cinnamon cup. Each were delicious. 

We will be back to try more flavors. Give it a try. You will be happy you went.
Great selection on the menu. The sampler is my favorite. Great sauce selection. Great tasting food. Get the banana pudding to finish off your meal

Eyebrows are very important , I only let him do my eyebrows because he actually does a really good job for them . He has a little Place next to pizza plus they do nails hair and eyebrows . But my fave is eyebrows highly recommend them here

My friends and I were passing through town looking for a place to grab dinner. We found this restaurant on yelp. The reviews were so correct. I had the pad see ew (it's not on the menu) but it was delishhhh. My other friends had the drunken noddles which they raved about. The owner himself was our server. He was full of energy and engaging. He later gave us some fried banana dessert on the house so we can all try it and there was 12 of us. Overall, great place it seems underrated but I would recommend everyone to try it.

After firing another local roofing company because we had no contact for 60 days (yikes) we did what we should have done in the first place and hired High Mountain Roofing Services.
