David has been in the business for 17+ years and it shows.  He is not only knowledgeable about the ins and outs of roofing, but he is a genuine human being and stands by his word.  He and his crew (including his amazing wife) took unbelievable care of our home.  The price was very competitive, the time to delivery was less than 5 days (and that included a holiday), the end product is beautiful and the service was outstanding.  I highly recommend this roofer.

I've been to Cucina Zapata three different times now and each time I come away amazed!   I've had the Cap'n Crunch Tilapia each time and it has been consistently delicious - well-cooked, enhanced just perfectly with Asian slaw and a mayo sauce with a ZING!   After reading the reviews on this site, my next choice in the chicken satay taco.  Well done, Cucina Zapata.  You are a welcome addition to the Drexel 'Food Truck Row' and I will continue to frequent your business.   HOW do they make such amazing food out of a TRUCK???    And - they are super-friendly to boot.    I also caution readers to not wait until late in the day to grab your lunch - you may be disappointed as I have been a few times.

Delivery service was prompt, the driver was friendly, pizza arrived hot, and all the food was better than we thought it might be, considering this is a corporate chain. Loved the pepperoni wedgie and thin crust pizza. Will definitely order again and use some of their great coupon deals that come in the mail.

Waiting here as a walk in and my name was on the screen displaying my name and time in mins (15 min wait). This was before lunch and I was aware of the lunch break time. The small lady who is always there walks out to the waiting area and turns off the lights and then goes back behind the door and put a closed sign up. No words spoken to me whatsoever. Just wow. Unacceptable to treat a person as if they were invisible after waiting there.
Nothing really special about this place.  The food is just ordinary, but not bad.  However, the price is a bit on the high side.  Good customer service though. On the silver lining, cute waitresses.
Selection is uninspiring, but, on the bright side, I can always find Rieslings for a decent price.  The service, on the other hand, is truly disappointing.

Fresh ! Fresh! Fresh ! Lol , not only is everything fresh as I stated , but the ingredients are great quality . You can tell they take great pride in everything they put together . We have not had one thing we did not  like. 
It also does not hurt that the owners  are lovely people.

Was really bummed that Genghis Grill went out of business so me and my mom tried this place. Didn't know anything about it but was still glad to get some good Mongolian stirfry in Hendersonville. It has the same concept as Genghis Grill with the bowls but has some different meat options it didn't have (such as scallops) which I liked. My bowl was really good and they were extremely accommodating to people with food allergies.

My mom has a peanut allergy so they made sure that her bowl didn't come near any peanuts and our waitress frequently checked on her to make sure her meal was good and that everything was ok. She even remembered our names and checked on us to see if we needed anything. The food was really good but the kindness from the staff was even better.

This place has happy hour everyday from 4-6pm and it's half off most things on the menu.  I love the sea bass!  Even though we go for happy hour our bill will still come out to be over $100.  Maybe we eat a lot but I think this place is pricey even with happy hour.  But it's a nice place to splurge on once and awhile.

We will undoubtedly be back. The service was awesome, our food was beautifully presented and delicious. The baba ghanouj was the best I've had in New Orleans and the hummus (also very good) was smooth and flavorful. The pita was fresh, warm and plentiful. Not to mention the delicious Lebanese tea. One of the freshest and most flavorful restaurants in the area.

We love Flamestone and are so happy to have a location in our neighborhood. Some of my favorites are Glazed salmon, Tuna Tower, Calamari, Ahi Tuna Salad, Tableside Guacamole (a must try!) and the Campfire S'mores! Plenty of options on their children's menu as well. This location is gorgeous and has two options for private party dining. Very excited for date nights, lunch meetings, brunch, family dinners, drinks with the girls, etc!
Good haircut, but messy. I think I got someone else's hair on me while in the chair.
By far the best seafood in Tampa!! Crab and seafood always fresh and full of flavor. Every time I visit Tampa I have to stop here!
Love this place!! Nancy, the owner, is amazing. Place is clean, tons of color options, awesome awesome awesome customer service.
Came here for the Banana Foster only and it was delicious. I ordered Banana Foster at other restaurants but they weren't as good. The dish looks so simple to make but it was the best here.
Service was kinda slow, the beef dip and the madame burger was pretty good! Corn chowder is amazing!
great service from our server, justin, and delicious food!! definitely will be going back soon!!

One of the BEST meals I've ever had in my life!!!!  Got combo, and I'm still in awe at how much I enjoyed every single thing on my plate. Service was so great and friendly, while providing food "orientation!" If I lived closer, I'd be a regular; maybe I still will be!

Love this coffee shop! Its so bright and energetic and the staff are so lovely & non pretentious.  Its becoming a new Saturday ritual to mosey down to district before the 104 street farmers market.   They also have several vegan options for food which is great. I had to take one star off because they only have almond milk as a replacement for dairy which I find can curdle & be bitter but other then that, this place is perfect.

We have eaten at Sugarfire many times.  Not sure why I never reviewed it.  We usually get the big meat plate.  It has pulled pork, ribs, brisket, sausage, and turkey.  All the sauces are good.  Its BBQ counter ordering.  Great sauces, greAt drinks, killer pies. Do it!!
The dentist was very nice but the office staff are rude and the practice is very unorganized....go elsewhere
I forgot to mention they charge .50 cents for onions on your cheesesteak, only in Mullica Hill!
Awesome local spot!  Such friendly staff and amazing food.  Make sure to get the crab bites and gumbo.  So delish!  Also one of the only bars that carries rajun canjun beer on tap.  Great experience!

Im back for breakfast, I had a veggie omelet added hollandaise sauce. Sophia was my waitress. She is a rock star  !!  She had several tables and one being a 10 top. She was on it.  all that my food was correct, it came fast and she was aways checking to see if I needed  my coffee topped off to keep it warm......there is also something to be said about all the wait staff....they are all friendly even to the tabes they are not serving.......and they are excellent at team work

This used to be one of my favorite places to grab lunch or dinner, that has slightly changed. Their pie is amazing, and i pray that they never change how they make it! However, the service has been sluggish as of late, the prices are through the roof compared to the diners in the area, and the salad bar, which was one of my favorite things about this place has went down hill. I was there just last week, and the rolls from the salad bar were a total disaster, hard as a rock, and they had none made fresh -- this was at dinner time mind you. They also used to have real crushed bacon as a salad topping, its now cheap processed "bits." I fully understand the cost of bacon, but for what they charge, come on..

I'll be back, but not for dinner service, just a slice of pie, because that's all they seem to do right anymore!

This is my new go-to for office lunches during Covid. Not only can I walk over and pick it up, but it's absolutely fabulous food. 

It's in a small building on the South side of Pima, west of Craycroft - don't blink, you'll miss it. 

Today I had the Brown Stew Chicken (see picture) and it was awesome. Comes with rice, steamed cabbage, bread & fried plantains. I've had the curry chicken there too - equally as awesome. 

They have tables outside as well if you want to eat there - great for takeout. 

High marks for this place next time you're looking for great Jamaican.

Not much to say about Pucketts, the service was great and food was delicious. The only thing I will say is that the service and food arrived fast.. like REALLY fast.. like drive-thru fast which was nice at first, but toward the end of the meal we felt very rushed. We didn't know that a band was playing at 8 and I'm guessing they needed to turn tables. We would have liked to stay and drink and listen to the band, but our server gave us our check so we assumed that wasn't an option.

My girls and I get milkshakes here all the time. Well we were down south and decided to have dinner. Had a coupon buy a double cheese burger get one free. So that's what my husband and I ordered. He also ordered a corn dog. The kids ordered 2 more burgers and a hot dog. 

Once the food was finished the corn dog was burnt so badly on the end  it crumbled. Since this was my husbands he moved on to his burger while they cooked him a new one. He opened the burger and the bottom bun was frozen. So I took it back up there said the bun is frozen. 

The girls  said sorry  papa he said I will never come here again. A restaurant that doesn't care about their food will not get my business. Our son said my bun iis frozen also. I'm just to hungry not to eat.

They brought out his food and the bottom of this hamburger bun was frozen also. 

They need a new cook!!! There is no reason a frozen bun should ever leave the kitchen.
Best hoagie shop around! They make the best Italian hoagies around. Only complaint I have is that they close early and aren't open everyday. Give them a try!!

Stopped in here for a beer during DNC convention week and found it to be a rather large place with a decent beer selection. I'm a fan of anywhere with multi double IPAs on draft so five stars for that alone. When it comes to the atmosphere of the place or the fact it feels super corporate, yah I don't recommend this for the beer culture loving type. bro bar meets brewery.

I'll make a long story short. My fiancée very much wanted a tattoo, and we booked through another place that will remain nameless. This other place made us wait 12 weeks for a consultation and wanted to make us wait another 12 weeks to get a tattoo the size of a quarter. All she wanted was a little red apple. 
I called Reno Tattoo Company and they got us in the next day. The place was clean, friendly, and professional. She loves her tattoo. We have both, since then, been back for 3 more tattoos (2 for me and 1 more for her). I am already planning on getting 3 more from them. 
Cody has done all of our tattoos for us, and we couldn't be happier. So be sure to request him. 
Talented, Friendly, Professional, and Clean sums it up when it comes to this place.

I usually go to Rembrandt's for just coffee, which they have amazing options for mocha's or just a great drip coffee. I recently been to their dinner service two different times and had an exceptional experience. I had the salmon which was amazing and a dessert putting which really couldn't have been better!!!!! I would give them a definite five stars recommend anybody who's looking for a great dining and Eagle to come to Rembrandt's

Amazing. The massages were great. Very clean. My wife worked was a manager at a spa and she was absolutely impressed. The soak after the massage is the best way you could possibly end a great massage. The price was well worth it. Nice little extras at no cost, steam room showers, Etc. 
I believe there is always room for improvement so my only improvement would be to take care of stocking the men's room, it was small things though, there was only 1 q-tip. They had razors, as cream to shave, some after shave would have been nice. That is me totally nit picking. It was a great experience.
excellent Mexican food. drinks are overpriced but it is the beach....

Are you kidding me!!! I order a salad...... tasted it and it was amazing. However, my husbands nachos came out and they looked amazing!!! So of course I had to taste and  that was it. I love nachos and hands down......... amazing.... aaaaamazzzing!!!! I'm moving here.

The prices were outrageous, BUT that being said, the fopd is amazing.

My favorite was the turtle soup, quail and the dessert was incredible!  I would definitely dine there again.

I recently visited Clearwater with a friend of mine and we stayed at the Holiday Inn so Jimmy's was very convenient for lunch as well as dinner. The first day we arrived we decided to just unpack and have dinner there instead of trying to find somewhere when we didn't know the area. We chose to sit outside, the weather was perfect and they had a man playing the steel drums. It was literally the perfect first night at the beach. The waitress was very efficient and the food was very good. My friend had the turkey club, I had a Cesar salad and a shrimp appetizer called Jolly Mon Shrimp, excellent! We both decided to have a Pina Colada which were also very good. We did go back to Jimmy's for lunch a few days later, the service wasn't good and there was bird poop on all the chairs and tables that wasn't cleaned but we cleaned it up and it didn't affect our meal,  the food was still excellent.  We did order drinks during the days we spent by the pool. The strawberry margarita and blue hurricanes were also very good.

This is perhaps my 4th negative experience with Hattie B's. I placed a pickup order for a large dark plate with a belgian waffle. I drove 10 minutes to get there and I drive 10 minutes back home. To my surprise when I get home I see the employees didn't pack any syrup for the waffle. Lucky me I didn't have any syrup at my house so I essentially wasted my money. Also, the waffle looked like it was just thrown in the box with no powdered sugar on it. On the menu it is described as being doused/covered with powdered sugar. 

Hattie B's has a terrible process in taking your pickup order. It's probably because they seem to have a long line you have to wait in so they don't prioritize pick up orders. If you're a tourist please go check out Boltons or Princes Hot Chicken which is across the street. It's much more authentic without the wait. 

I tried calling Hattie B's to solve this issue but I have been left on hold for 12 minutes. Finally a guy picked up at 12 mins and then said please hold. Your customer service is terrible. I've been in the restaurant industry for years. Please step your game up. Again, if you're a tourist spend your money at a more authentic chicken restaurant. The food is tasty but when the staff clearly don't care then you should take your business elsewhere.

This place has run of the mill bar food.  The best thing I've had here has been the grouper sandwich.  The vegetables I had on the side were very salty.  They have a large bar and lots of TVs.  The service has been good, but I'd rather get better food somewhere else.
Visiting from Boston was craving Mexican food. The customer service was wonderful. The tacos I would give 3 out of 5 stars. Street corn was sooo good!
The stewed chicken...Delicious!  This was my first visit. I come to this area every couple weeks, so I'll definitely be back to try their other items.

Weelll....he was an hour late (and didn't call me...I called him after 20 minutes, and then he said he'd be 20 more and then rolled in 20 after that.)   That said, he was super nice, very smart and committed to getting the job done really well.  I'd use him again.

OKAY FOR THE WINE - HORRIBLE SERVICE - AVOID AT ALL COSTS THE FOOD.  WE INSTEAD WENT TO STEAK & SHAKE AFTERWARDS WHERE THE FOOD WAS MUCH BETTER.  LETS HOPE THAT THE KITCHEN NIGHTMARES - GORDON RAMSAY LIKE CONSULTANT CAN HELP TURN THIS PLACE AROUND.

 I would give Shiraz 1.5 stars.  I had a mixed overall  experience at Shiraz.  The concept sounded interesting and my wife, my friends, and I decided to give it a try. 

 PROS:  Shiraz is in the new and trendy Arts & Design District of Carmel, IN.  The place looks new, has two levels, and the upstairs section where we were seated felt like a neat, trendy living room.  Interesting/ good concept where there are wine dispensers and you get a swipe/ account card and can try different wines.  You can choose small, medium, or large wine fills. 

CONS - THE FOOD:  It needs a serious overhaul.  We tried to order several small plates for a group.  The waiter came back on several occasions after 20-30 minutes stating that they were out of what we ordered.  The owner then stated that everything was on the menu.  Then more feedback from the kitchen and waiter: So with 2-3 not available, and we ordered alternatives.  The lobster mac n cheese for $15 was not worth it.  It was like a dry store bought mac n cheese box where water was added.  The cheese was very little and tasteless and there was only two or three very small pieces of lobster - which took some effort to find.  The crab cakes tasted very fishy and we wondered it they were spoiled.  There were also a couple of shell fragments in crab cakes.  The beef skewers were very dried out, burned, and overcooked. The flat-breads looked like they came out of a freezer/box from the grocery store.  The toppings were skimpy.  We returned the food and got our money back.  

CONS - SERVICE:  While we got our food refunded, the owner (older lady) got upset at our criticism of the food, yelled back at us, and called us Midwestern Hicks.  I disagree - my wife and I are foodies from the Chicago area.  We have traveled internationally and several times to California to San Francisco and Sonoma County - where the owner claims the concept came from.  

GORDON RAMSAY-LIKE CONSULTANT:  We talked to a gentleman there and he mentioned that he was a consultant hired by the owner. He was nice and professional, and agreed that the food on the menu needed an overhaul. He said the owner had threatened to fire him several times when he offered her constructive criticism.  

OVERALL:  This place has potential, but the food offerings need to be improved or dropped all together. Also, the owner needs to be more professional like the consultant when offered both compliments and criticism.  The food at Steak and Shake was much better.

Not coming here again. I have to pay extra for them to vacuum out dog hair and the price changes every time I come in. I always have to dry off the Jeep when they are done. Water spots everywhere. They left the back gate open and the back door.  I will have to find another touch less car wash in town. I'm done with this place.

The reviews are pretty spot on. I will say the taste and texture of their pizza is similar to an undercooked Tony's Pizza. You know... The pizza we ALL had in elementary school. Just imagine that with over cooked/stale crust. Enjoy your drunk ness though
Jema runs a clean and on-time operation! Everyone there is professional and I always come out looking better than when I went in.

I got to town a little late and didn't feel like driving all around to find a good place so I decided to give it a try. We both had the filet mignon and shared the creamed spinach and scalloped potatoes. The fillets were slightly over cooked and a bit dry, they could take a lesson from Flemings on how to season a steak. The spinach was ok but the potatoes are tasty. Over all not terrible and not great.
Don't go for the the whiskey cocktails. Decent whiskey selections at over retail price. Food was pretty good,

I would love to give this place 5 stars because we had a lovely stay until the maid either stole from our room or threw out around $200 worth of souvenirs.  As I am sure you have heard before, when these things happen the hotel claims little responsibility, so we will return home without gifts for the kids while they "investigate."  I would have never expected something like this from such a nice hotel.  What a horrible way to end a trip.

If you're coming to Bocelli's come prepared with a bottle of wine and an appetite. This cozy BYOB located in the old Gwynedd Valley train station is one of the best places in the area for good Italian cooking. 

All of their salads and appetizers are delicious and their specials change constantly to reflect whatever the freshest ingredients at their cooks disposal is. Often they'll bring out a complimentary appetizer in addition to what you order. Their main courses are all superb, the pasta is all cooked perfectly and all of the fish dishes are incredibly fresh. After dinner stick around for a complimentary shot of homemade limoncello!

This place was such a great experience. We wanted to try a new place, decided on Italian and landed on barra rossa. I like the big open windows that provide a nice street view while you eat. 

The service here was exceptional. Our server Devon was bright, friendly, and came over to check in often, just really wonderful all around. She also made great recommendations! The manager even stopped by at one point. All in all, the best service I've seen at any restaurant in recent memory. 

The food was also just unreal. Wanted to get the prix fix at first, but we decided to share a pizza instead. The pucillo pizza was great. The arugula balanced the prosciutto so well, and made for a unique and delicious pie. I thought the prices were very reasonable and the portions were generous. I could probably write 2-3 things about each dish pictured, every single thing was absolutely delicious, but I'll just say this place is for sure worth trying. 6/5 if I could!

My experience with Southeast Financial was awesome!  My husband and I have a  complicated financial portfolio and yet Southeast, unlike others, took the time to understand and unravel our situation to make everything work well for us.  We now have our dream RV!  Thank you Southeast!!!!
Great tacos and awesome salsa with lots of flavor! Next time I go I will definitely be trying the tacos el pastor. The price is very good too.

During the Coronavirus pandemic I understand the need to limit people in the store. Before entering the sign says no more than 10 people including employees. There were no customers and only 5 employees and this one sale associate had an attitude not wanting to let us in the shop to look at bike accessories. One guy behind the counter spoke up and said it's ok with the amount of people inside but this sales associate had a bad attitude the entire time and felt we were telling him how to do his job. We were wearing masks and wanted to browse for a few things. Nobody was in there shopping but us. I hope he gets fired or they go out of business for their poor customer service when I am trying to support a local business.

It's a cute place and the concept is nice and very unique. The staff was nice and it wasn't too busy at all. The chicken just wasn't good to me. The sauce was okay but I guess my expectations where too high especially for the price. Maybe if I'm in the area again I'll give it another try and see what happens
Dr. Pedrick and her team are EXCELLENT! Between the service and the most updated equipment, select Dr. Pedrick if you haven't done so - yet!

Beach City apartments located directly across the street from Santa Barbara City College is the most ideal location for student living for many reasons. I've been a resident at Beach City for several months now and have had an unbelievable experience. The staff at Beach City go out of their way to make sure you have a pleasant living experience. They always cooperate with any problems or concerns. For example, my apartments sink was clogged and Beach City was quick to respond and fix the problem. Apart from a 30 second walk to class and being able to spend time between classes either at the beach,pool, or on Green St. playing volleyball with friends: life here has been quite relaxing. Beach City is lenient with rules because they trust us as young adults in college to make smart decisions and trust the property, enabling us to enjoy Santa Barbara to the max. Beach City has a beautiful property with palm tree's, volleyball court, ping pong tables, hop-scotch, pool, and lounge area makes every school day feel like a vacation. 5 Star rating for sure if you're a City College student who wants the convenience of living across the street from campus and experiencing Santa Barbara to its full beauty.

NO _ _ DO NOT EAT HERE_ _

This is the absolute worst place to eat in the entire country, not just the West End of Nashville. I walked in and could not tell who worked there. I sort of feel bad for the people who work there. How the heck are they able to be there all day and not be physically ill from the food-borne bacteria that is clinging to every single inch of the place. 
Rude wait staff, they didn't even offer me a menu to order from, so in desperation to have some soup, I walked around the buffet. The steam seemed to indicate that the food was hot and fresh - but my culinary friend - do not be fooled. This food was cooked HOURS ago and was ROOM temperature. I sat down and took one bite, and spit it out on my plate. Even the soup was not even remotely warm.
I stood up and walked to the counter and said 'I am not paying' and walked out. Do not eat here - please for all that is sacred. Go anywhere and eat, but do not eat here.

I went here last night with my son . I heard the food was good. After waiting over an hour and a half for our food to come we finally left. 
Our waitress didnt even come over to tell us that it still wasn't ready. Another one did. 
I understand it is busy with kids coming back to school but a table of four that was sat down after us got their food and the attention from the manager we got nothing but the hard chips they put out. 
Horrible !!!!!
One star because it wouldn't let me post without. 
I give it a negative !!!!!

Went here with two friends on a weekend night around dinner time. Between the three of us, we ordered three entrees, a bottle of wine, and three beers. The food was fine and service was great, and our night would have been perfect, if it hadn't been for the following: about 50 minutes after we sat down (20 minutes after we finished eating), the server told us that their manager was asking when we were going to be leaving. We didn't want to immediately get up and leave (we still had drinks), so we continued our evening and finished our drinks. For the next 10 minutes, we were very conscious of employees talking about us and staring at us, and even heard a server tell some customers, "they won't leave," and gesture towards us. So, after finishing our drinks and an hour after we were seated, we got up and left. A server on our way out said a very sarcastic "thankkkksss."

If this review was for food or service (from our server), this would be a 4 star review. However, it would not be fair to rate this restaurant more than 1 star when three people, trying to enjoy our weekend and spending our hard earned money on a nice meal, all felt so mistreated and unwanted that it spoiled our night. I don't know if it's because we are younger than most of their clients (we're in our mid 20s), or if they just don't know how to handle a busy night, but it was an awful end to a good meal. Perhaps we did not spend enough money for them to let us have the table for more than 50 minutes. Either way, we were nothing but polite, good-tipping patrons who were treated like we were totally unwanted.

I usually do not write long reviews, but it is necessary this time. Take the time to read this, and you will understand the RIGID program at The Fox, then see the end cartoon.  I got the cartoon idea from my friend Ron M. (Master Yelper and cool dude!

This was my 4th time here.
     
      They follow their rules, and are diligent about them, in some cases the point of being overly "direct."  This works for and against you, the customer, depending upon what your goal is for your evening.  
     
     You want to stop by and have a drink after a dinner elsewhere with a date for an hour or so? It will cost you $50 plus a tip - pretty steep. ($3 for Valet, $10 each for cover and $22 for 2 drinks+tax, and a $4 tip)

     You decide to have DINNER HERE, (see food review, below) you get a reserved table, a spot to sit all evening, and it all rolls up to a whole evening experience. HOWEVER YOU STILL PAY $10 EACH FOR COVER.  Still its an above average experience - for your date. For me, (the "GUY PAYING THE BILL" and the person that decides whether to bring a date here again!) it would have been nice if I could have left there feeling "great" too.... - it was "Just above OK" for me due to the way the cover/dinner rules/valet are handled.

2.  At the narrow entry way, a "Bouncer/Doorman/Rule enforcer type guy" is blocking entry behind while you speak to a very polite hostess.  In a wider entry way, maybe this would not look/feel so "unsettling."  I'm 6'6" weigh 230, and I rarely have a feeling like this.  Maybe it had to do with the guy pointing out (a bit loudly) in front of my date that "Your shirt needs a collar!" rather than smiling, and whispering to me "hey, in the future, we require a collar"... It was a $104 Tommy Bahama shirt...without a collar. For the record, collar rule - good -  how the message was delivered -bad-  on top of a $23 pre-entry routine.

INSIDE: 2 band areas, both very different, both very nice! Clean, intimate lighting, nice 'vibe" in each room. Nice, modern, clean restrooms with TV screens, very cool, very high end.

SERVICE: Excellent, and our waitperson was attentive, polite and just plain nice. 

FOOD:  We ordered crab cake appetizer (excellent), and steak on toast with blue cheese (good) appetizer. A bit later, we ordered the blue cheese house made chips (good).  We each had two drinks, the house Cabernet "the Show" is good.  My friend had 2 cocktails, and was happy with what she ordered.  

MUSIC: The jazz quartet is very good, and the volume during the time we were eating was at a level where we could still talk.  After most diners had finished, they turned it up, and that worked for us. Very professional group, and very talented.

OVERALL: We had a nice time, we tipped the piano player well, and he signed a CD and gave it to us....very nice!  That made the evening for my friend, and that was the goal of the evening, that she had a nice time.  I got over the initial "bad vibe" and enjoyed the evening, too.


After the evening was over:

            O   O         "Thanks for the nice kiss!"   :^)
           / I \/oo\   
           /  \   II
Great place to swing by and have some delicious food no wait at the bar highly recommend the mac & cheese, fries end of their chicken sandwich with avocado.
Lamb Burger was pretty nice but do yourself a favor and have an omelette with gyro meat, feta cheese and 3 other goodies... you won't regret it.
Food was delicious and fresh. Staff was kind . Next time I'm in Philadelphia center City I will definitely order from them.

This place was a surprise to find one of the first times I came to Philly and now I try to come back every time I'm in town to explore more of their many vegan-friendly options.

You haven't lived if you haven't tried their Coconut Club. Tofu in exchange for turkey and crispy smoky coconut instead of bacon. The texture is spot on and the flavor profile is fantastic. Also a solid veggie burger! Next up on my list to try? The "Veal" Parmesan (it's just portobello mushrooms, don't fret animal loving friends).

As a fan of good beer/wine, their selection also gets the thumbs up. The quality of food you get for the cost puts most Boston equivalents to shame. 

Great staff, cool customers, and awesome bar-talk eavesdropping. Check it out.

What a perfect spot for my birthday dinner! I love Italian food and hadn't really tried anyplace in Indy that I loved yet, but I think Maialina is going to be one I frequent quite a bit!

Reservations are recommend - we were able to get a seat at the bar right after opening at 5, but next time I won't walk in, especially if I have more than two in my party. 

Started off with a strawberry drink- it was light and refreshing, but I would have liked a stronger strawberry taste. 

The food was absolutely delicious though. I had the sausage pasta, which came with rigatoni, broccolini, red pepper flakes and an olive oil based sauce. A nice heat to it with the red pepper and spicy sausage and portion sizes were generous with enough for leftovers the next day. My mom had the ravioli with pesto cream sauce and said her meal was also really, really good. 

Great service and a nice atmosphere- definitely a place for date night or celebrating something special.
I really like my haircut done by Jess.  Next time I will be happy to return to make an appointment with her.  Thank you

I have been working with Jon and his partner for about 1 year and I am so pleased with their work.

They are professional, prompt and fair with pricing.  Jon keeps in contact with information pertaining to appointment time, materials needed and the amount of time each job would entail.  He and his assistant also clean up during and at the completion of each job.

I have employed Express Power for dedicated lines for light fixtures, Ring Doorbell, kitchen outlets, counter top lights, sconces indoor and outdoor. Plus they just recently installed my  security camera.

Jon I must say you and your partner, are the BEST1

I will always employ Express Power as my personal electricians.

Had a Groupon and having had botox before knew I had to get 48 to get results I wanted. Love Love love entire staff very warm and answered all my questions about all their other procedures very thoroughly without trying to sell me anything.  Dr B was very friendly did not seem rushed to get on to any other patients.  I felt like the only patient in the office he took his time to answer all my questions.  Loved the office so much I decided to do dual fraxel for my age and acne spots ..everyone at work comments on how great my skin now looks my face is clear of dark spots for first time in 30 years and I have done deep chemical peels extensions before nothing gave such excellent results . I am 1000 percent happy with the results

I have been to this Counter location three times and the food is decent but what the service is terrible.  Every time it is so slow and it takes a server forever to acknowledge us.  Our most recent visit was last week.  First off, there was very few people in the restaurant.  We were there about 1:30/2 for a late lunch.  Our server took forever to come to our table for drinks.  My wife ordered a milkshake and he never even got it til he was almost done with his meal.  He also ordered an egg on his burger but they forgot it.  We asked the server to remove the charge from the bill before she even brought it but of course it was still on the bill.  We asked her again to remove it and she didn't and still charged us.  I had purchased two $20 gift cards from through the Idaho Statesman discounted gift card event they had a while back. When I went to redeem them she only redeemed them for $12 each, which is the discounted price I had purchased them for.  I tried to explain that was how the Statesman gift card event worked, that I really had paid for two $20 cards.  She had no idea what I was talking about so safe to say my gift cards went to waste.  If you are going to participate in a discounted gift card program at least educate your employees about how it works.  Very disappointed and will not be back.  Three strikes.

So insanely rude. They don't listen to your order, they're talking the whole time you order. Then they say "huhh? What do you want" like maybe if you listened you would know the first time. Then you get to the window they don't even tell you how much they just ask for your money. I've been here about four/five times and every time they've forgotten something in my order then get mad about it even though they don't listen when you tell them the order at the window. Need better workers man
The food is solid. It is not an exceptional experience in any sense, but I love that you can sit outside and watch the park during the spring and summer time.
Great beer selection, great spot and low key inside.  Games to play or just chat with music in background.  Great outdoor spot for warm weather with band space.

Such a disappointment..My fiancé and I have been in New Orleans almost two years. A coworker of his recommended this restaurant to him about six months after we moved here. But with work and life happening we put it off until this past weekend, when we finally to come out to Marrero and give it a try. As we were driving, I was on Yelp looking at the menu and reading the reviews. I mentioned to him that they weren't great and maybe we should just go grab something else. We got there and the outside is okay, nothing special. The host opens the door and greets us, she was very welcoming and takes us to out seat. Our server comes over and takes our drink order, French 75 for myself and Anita Amber for him. She brings our drink and we order boudin balls as our appetizer. For our entrees I order Chicken stuffed boudin and he order the prime rib special and they both come with side salads. We get our boudin balls and I gotta say I wasn't impressed, lacked flavor. Then we get our side salad, I normally don't expect much from a side salad but it was sad, just a few leaves thrown together. Then we get our entrees, my chicken(comes with jambalaya) looked so good. I looked over at his dish and his looked at his steak and it looked a bit weird. Like I said my chicken looked so delicious, I cut my chicken and ate a small piece. Okay let me tell you, I've tasted chicken like this when I first learned how to cook.. because it wasn't cooked!! It was chewy and all I wanted to do is spit it back out. But it was too late and I just swallowed it. I cut a few more pieces and just looked over it, and it wasn't cooked.. we waited 30+ minutes for our food, so we didn't care to wait longer. The jambalaya was good but not great and that's all I could eat, chicken was left uneaten. His steak was bland, nothing to write about. Our server asked if it was good, we just said yes. We wanted dessert but I was so grossed out I just wanted to go home, we even took the food to go to throw it out ourselves. On the way home we were just discussing how this was the worst restaurant we've been to here in Louisiana. Our drinks and service was good but we definitely won't be back.

Stumbled upon this place exploring Bourbon Street, first time in NOLA. Let me just say that the staff was wonderful, helpful, cheerful and attentive! We got the boudin balls for an appetizer and they were delicious! The dipping sauce was so good that we saved it to dip our fries in for our entrees. The drinks were strong and creative - watermelon infused vodka made the drink taste like blended watermelon. The catfish was so tender and flavorful, exact what catfish should taste like! Our waitress (who we absolutely adored but can't remember her name) gave me free bread pudding since it was my birthday, bless her! Would highly recommend, cute place with quieter ambiance compared to the rest of Bourbon street with delicious food and boozy drinks!

I called about a week inquiring about an estimate to replace the rear differential pinion bearing on my FJ. I was quoted $2400. Since then I've received other quotes: $600 from Advanced Automotive, Driveline Services, $700, Rear Ends $700, and even Carson City Toyota $865. The price Reno dept quoted is more than 3 times the amount quoted anywhere else, and $1635 more than another Toyota dealership. As a female who feels I'm getting ripped off often anyway in the world of car mechanics, it's frustrating to know that the service dept representing the make of my vehicle is in the business of this type of gross over charging. It's shameful.

While visiting Nashville, some friends and i decided to come here. I had no idea what it was, but was shocked when I got there! This is SUCH a cool concept and an awesome place to hang out. I wish we had something like this in VA. People were working on their laptops, hanging out with friends, drinking at the bar, stopping in for coffee, and bowling in the back. The atmosphere was literally perfect for any situation. If I lived in Nashville, I would spend way too much time here.

The Missouri Botanical Garden is such a beautiful place to spend the day wandering around with family and friends. I love feeding the gigantic fishies by the Japanese garden (only .25 and you get a handfull of what I think is cat food) and let the laughs ensue. I once saw a guy there that loved feeding the fishies more than I do and even offered some of his cat food he brought himself!
The Whitaker Music Series is great fun and a great place for a date or when you are looking for some summer fun everyone in the family can enjoy. The garden gets packed on these nights! You bring your own seats or a blanket and enjoy the music and people watching. You can bring your own treats like wine and cheese or sandwhiches and sodas or you can cough up the $$ and buy brisket sandwhiches, sno cones, or an arrary of beverages. Check back on the mobot.org website to find upcoming events!

I waited until after my third visit here to put this up. I wanted to be sure this place had the chops to stay here after the last business in this location folded after a short time. 

Based on what I've eaten so far, I do hope this place sticks. 

He's doing not only a full take out menu, he's also doing a lunch buffet Monday to Friday for $9.95.  The buffet includes your choices of about 4 meat entrees, wings, potatoes, and pasta with meatballs.  It also includes soups, salad, and bread.  Oh by the way, it also includes your choice of pizza. 

I was stunned the first time I had it. I couldn't believe he was offering all of this for the price. 


Everything I've had has been of pretty high quality. The wings are charbroiled and baked, and they come out juicy with good flavor. Most everything is made on the lighter side so you don't leave there feeling like you overindulged (Tony, the owner, tells me he doesn't like to fry anything unless he has to).  The soup has been excellent. They make the house salad to order. The bread is toasted nicely drizzled with olive oil. And, they offer more pizza slices than just the basic cheese and pepperoni for you to try. You can actually get a more gourmet slice out of the deal. Service has always been very accommodating too. 

The best thing is, you don't have to go for the buffet. The full take out menu is available so you can just go for a couple of slices if you want for lunch. I haven't been for dinner yet, but they offer a pretty extensive dinner menu as a BYOB. 

I like that they're trying to do something different than the basic pizza and sub shop in this spot.  It is worth your time to try them out.

I started here when they first opened and used to really like working out here but it is getting progressively worse and less tolerable especially at peak hours. 

1. Between 4-6 on weekdays it can be a madhouse. In the last year a lot of kids have started here who have zero gym etiquette (4-6 people on multiple racks with no one lifting for an hour - reminds me of my high school weight room)

2. Trainers will literally walk up to an area where paying members are working out / using equipment and kick you off to work with a client. This has happened to me on multiple occasions, really kills a workout flow. 

Like I said, I used to really like working out here. It's sad that I find it frustrating when I go to the gym now. Management could easily fix these problems with a simple talk to trainers to respect members workouts and a conversation with new members to explain what gym etiquette is (wipe down equipment after sweating on it, don't hog machines for hours, try and stay busy on equipment you're using especially if it's busy and people are waiting, basic stuff really.. apparently some people need to be told.)

This was a fun thing to do in Philly during the snow storm. It was a cool way to learn how they make their own vodka and whiskeys right in a 900sf basement. It was pretty interesting. The host was pretty good. He obviously knew his whiskey. The bartender was funny and made a strong drink lol. He only used 3 ingredients and it was hitting! At the end they give you a tasting of all the things they make at that distillery. My favorite was the pineapple vodka. Very delicious  and made with real pineapples. Yummy! We ordered the vouchers on Groupon so check them out at a discounted rate. Peep pics below

My mom and I took the Creole and Crescent Tour with Laura and I highly recommend it to anyone looking for something to do other than getting hammered in the French Quarter. You get to learn some history of the city and its neighborhoods while riding through them. And Laura was amazing. Hands down my favorite part of my trip. Thank you Free Wheelin!

We had the terrine, the kohlrabi and mizuna salad, the King Mackerel, the daily cochon pork special of Kassler Style pork chop, and the bacon braised field peas.  Everything was amazing and we had to go talk to the kitchen afterwards because we were so happy.  20 years in the Chicago hospitality scene didn't prepare me for this kind of execution, just fantastic.  I am sad because I don't live here.

The best pizza in Fairmount.  Their selection of pizza by the slice (under $3 a slice) has toppings more reminiscent of Italy than a typical American pizza place.  

I would have gone 5 stars, but their cheesesteaks aren't that great.

Really Good Quality Chinese food. Although I love Chinatown, the quality and the not-so-greasy (fresh) food at this restaurant is hard to beat. My friends from out of town usually request to meet there. I've been going there for years and it's always been my secret place for Chinese food since it's up in the suburbs. I'm usually eating in the city and having a glass of wine (or a bottle) could become pretty pricey with a few friends. We usually take advantage of the BYOB with the wine and spirits right there.

We share it family style so everyone gets to try a bit of everything. Our favorite starter is Chicken with Lettuce Wraps since it's not too heavy and we enjoy the concept of using lettuce as your edible bowl or wrap. Sometimes, we fulfill our craving and go for some of the steaks, Orange flavored beef, or the soft shell crabs. The steak is always tender and tasty and the soft shell crabs are crispy even with the sauce. The kids usually enjoy the General Tso Chicken and the Lo Mein. I've tried the chicken at several other places but most places are too soggy, too sweet, barely any meat and too much batter. Sometimes I treat myself to Seafood w/ Crispy Pan Friend Noodles. I would say that is one of my favorites because the noodles at the rim are crispy yet the middle has a nice sauce that softens it. The seafood is fresh. 

I also like getting the moo shu pork since the kids are picky with veggies. Everything is cut small and mixed together so when the kids have fun making the wraps while eating the veggies.  The owners are usually there and the kids love receiving a paper fan from them. Although it breaks soon after departing, it's good enough for them.

I always love going to East Nashville restaurants. The atmosphere here is so hipster. Red bicycle is awesome. I got the Florentine Omelet and the Nutella Crepe with bananas. The omelet was very heavy so you can probably share with someone if you are also getting the dessert crepe. Also, dogs are allowed on the patio! As a new pet owner, this makes me so happy!

The garlic knots are dee-lish-ous! I have always had the antipasto salad here for lunch (it comes with 2 or 3 pieces of wonderful garlicky bread with cheese sauce). The pizza looks good but I love me a good antipasto ... It's never very busy here, which is a shame.

Nice place, seems family run.

They're menu isn't huge but what I had was really good. Not the best I've had but better than most. Too bad I don't live closer, I could be a regular. The tripe tacos are some of the best I've had in the states, order them crunchy! I think they might only be available on the weekends though.

Maybe I have just been unlucky, but I didn't think the food was that great on either of my visits.  My husband brought home takeout and the only thing I cared for was the soup and the steamed dumplings.  The entrees we ordered were horrible.  First visit we got the General Tsos Chicken and second time I got the Honey Garlic Chicken. The honey garlic chicken seemed like leftovers from the night before... Very tough and it had a weird, almost burnt flavor.  I think the restaurant refried leftover chicken from the previous day or the chicken sat under a heat lamp all day.

I thought it was really odd that not all of the employees were in uniform... One guy walked out of the kitchen wearing sandals!  The restaurant is in dire need of remodeling and spring cleaning.  The restaurant has these huge, unsightly fish tanks with tilapia and crabs.  We watched an employee scoop out a tilapia from the tank... The fish tried to escape from him and splashed water all over the wall and floor.  It was absolutely depressing watching the other fish mourn their friend.  The fish seemed very aware of their fate. On the plus side: the fish and crab are very fresh at China Yuan!

This place seems to be really popular so I guess I am ordering the wrong things off the menu. One of these days I am going to visit for dim sum so I can hopefully revise my review.
Delicious Greek food and fantastic desserts! Eat in or drive through at Commercial Way location!

I feel like this restaurant has been here since the dawn of time but I've never checked it out. Finally my friend randomly took me over the weekend. I do see now that they apparently had a health code violation. Oh well. I've literally eaten meatballs that were cooked out of a barely washed pot in the middle of an unnamed village in Eastern Thailand that were probably sitting out all day. I'm not THAT scared. Although I do wonder what the violation was for exactly. Maybe I'll leave it a mystery.

Anyway this place is so damn cheap. I am just reviewing the bakery side. We bought 4 pork buns, 2 taro cakes, 2 egg tarts, 1 chocolate cake slice, and 1 coconut pastry. It came out to a whopping $12.50! Extremely cheap eats. Everything was delicious except for the coconut pastry, it just tasted like pure butter. The pork buns were my favourite because I love me a bit of sweet n savoury. 

The lady working there was very sweet and knew everyone who came in the door. I like that kind of local relationship building. It only comes from places that have been around for a while. 

I would definitely come back to buy things from this bakery. I did not get a chance to try the restaurant, but maybe one day!

People love this place. It reminds of the food you would find at a restaurant in the 80s when your parents would take you to a place where they got a steak and you got a burger. I liked the potato a lot but the burger was good because it reminded me of childhood, nothing revolutionary. The rum drinks are decent though and I'd come back to appease my friends that love this place.

Our family came here for Easter Brunch. As far as buffets go,it was well above average, with a lot of choices. My only disappointment was with the crepes. I wanted a savory crepe, and was faced with your typical omelet bar offerings, and no sauces. they had a lot more for the desert crepes. Everything else i had was wonderful. They rotated the plates often, so everything was fresh. The service was excellent. The staff went out of their way to make our holiday visit special.

The staff was very nice and attentive; They were constantly aware of our tables needs and requests. Thank you especially to Taijha for being so sweet and kind, we had an amazing time celebrating fathers day. We will be back to the restaurant soon.

Before becoming a mom, I loved buying clothes for myself but now I can't imagine anything more fun than shopping for clothes for my little girl. Carter's has adorable options for little ones so be prepared to shop longer than expected and most likely buy more items than you originally intended... 

My favorite thing about Carter's is that they are ALWAYS having some type of sale. I scored some amazing items just last weekend when they did a "One Day Only: Early Black Friday Sale" where everything was at least 60% off. Not only do they have great sales but every time you shop, you receive a new coupon for your next purchase at both Carter's and Oshkosh. Don't forget to sign up for the rewards program to receive "Fun Cash" for future purchases-- it's easy to join and your rewards get emailed directly to you!

Staff has always been friendly and even when I can't find my coupons, they usually apply some sort of discount that they currently have going on.

Another plus is that the store always has holiday themed clothing options, whether it's your baby's first Thanksgiving, Christmas, or 4th of July, they've got what you're looking for!
The rice paper wrapper filled with shrimp and chicken is just the best thing I've tasted

Pros:  barista was friendly and the place was very clean. Internet worked well and was fast.  My drink I ordered (I always get the chai tea latte) was delicious as always.

Cons: someone else accidentally took my drinks so I ended up having to wait extra while they made me a new one. Not necessarily Starbucks fault but still a little frustrating.  Also they did have a small wait in line to order (about 5 minutes) which wasn't horrible.
Best authentic Italian food in the area. Food is always amazing. Staff is excellent and very attentive. Highly recommend Bombato Cioccolatino for dessert, heavenly.

Short and sweet.

For $249 a night, there are better downtown Indy hotels.  The room was outdated, smelled musty, small and not nearly as nice as I remember (the last time I stayed I was 21, so I had a different "perception" then).  The beds  are the same, comfy but I had full size beds, much prefer a king.  Yes, they are very nice, but if that is all they base their prices on, SO NOT WORTH IT.

Stay somewhere else.  If you land this hotel on Hotwire, you are good to go, but otherwise, don't pay full price. The staff was average.  Other than the beds and location, I think you need to try something else for that kind of money per night (recommend Marriott or Hilton).
This is my favorite burger place so far! They serve authentic American food at the busy corner of Bourbon and Dumaine. Stop by for some fries and burgers. You're gonna love it!

During hard times like this with everything going on with covid , I can't go visit my family in Santa Barbara I live in Palm Springs .
I order a delivery basket with a happy birthday ballon for my daughter on her birthday and the basket was beautiful but the balloon didn't arrive with my purchase ,I was disappointed because they charge delivery service even after $80 purchase ans I'm fine with paying but I expect for a complete delivery .
I contact the florist and they didn't even care loosing a client they told me that my daughter can stop by and get the ballon (drive out there when I paid already for the services ) how was that fair . I didn't like how they handle service and I know all about costumer service .

Exit escape rooms have given us some great escape room experiences so far. 
Our first room was Division 37- but before I get into our feelings on the room I think it's important to mention some things that created our positive first impression. This place has a small lobby/waiting area but has 5 different rooms! Firstly I so appreciate that they put a star difficulty level on their rooms - this makes it really simple as a first timer to know what room to pick. The staff are friendly and quick to greet you as you enter. We had some discount off cards and they were applied really easily and taken off our bill- which we paid at the beginning before we did our room. The orientation is so well done- I really appreciate that they take the time to show you the locks you're going to encounter in the rooms as well as clarifying that the laminated cards are not to be removed if they are stuck to a box or something. Great low down on what to expect. 
Into the room! Such fantastic props in Division 37- that really stuck out to my husband who is an avid Airsoft guy. He really enjoyed it. We only had 4 people in our group but that was probably just right as the space in the room is a little tight even for 4. All the rooms at Exit take 2-6 people. We literally were on the last clue and very nicely the guy let us finish and solve it to have that accomplished feeling since we were so class to the end. 
The second room we did was Medieval- we thought the idea of choosing your own story either following the path of Merlin or King Arthur was so unique! Something we have not heard any other escape rooms doing yet! You have to find your hints and the staff are quick to come aid you. We found the puzzles in this room actually harder than Division 37 and had to use all three hints on our quest so that caused a bit of frustration. 
Overall I enjoyed this escape room and am excited to see that they are looking at expanding in Edmonton. We would definitely recommend this place to people who have never done an escape room before because they create a good first timers experience.

Worst fucking Wingstop I ever been to. Rude ass little children working or just collecting a check cuz they ain't doing no work. Shit always be wrong, always missing the ranch and THEY NEVER PICK UP THE PHONE. It's so sad because I live so close and love Wingstop but this location is terrible. it's a bad experience every time I go no matter the hour. Veterans is better

Favorites: Chips and Guac (generous portion and delicious), breakfast burrito (huge!) and chicken tacos (tender and flavorful).
I could do without the veggie tacos, no bueno...I think there were carrots in it? Or weirdly hard sweet potato that tasted like carrots; I'm not sure. Though the pico was generously piled on which I appreciated. 
Also, I love their homemade mild and halloween hot sauces! 
Service is always friendly and quick!

This is a great neighborhood spot. Now that the weather has warmed up, do yourself a favor and grab a taco to enjoy on the sidewalk tables as you people watch.
These folks know their stuff and are very pleasant to work with! They were helpful on phone and I asked about draw knives... and in the store. Good humored as well.

I have been here numerous times with my family (my wife and 3 boys under 8), extended family (all nine of us), myself (ahh... a quiet meal), and clients (introducing them to local restaurants)...  everyone has left raving about the meal they just had. Whether breakfast, lunch, dinner, or pancakes at anytime of the day, always a great meal.

Add to that great service, a pleasant setting, clean bathrooms, a nice salad bar, and fantastic desserts. This is a gem in the growing local food scene. 

Make mine Pottstown!

I love Cesare's. I go every single time I come down to visit. I've had the pappardelle, the fettuccine Alfredo, the fra diavolo, the lasagne... the list goes on. All have been very very good. It seems pricy but you end up with leftovers for days, so it evens out. The oil and bread they bring out to start is somehow SO GOOD. I don't know how they do it. Garlicky, peppery, delicious. Salads there are good too, but nothing special. The wait staff are extremely professional and kind. I would 100% recommend Cesare's, especially when you need a break from fried clam strips and shrimp baskets on Clearwater Beach.
Wine was great and the view was simply the best. We watched the sunset with a glass of wine.
This pizza is amazing! Every time I have pizza anywhere else, it doesn't compare. The guys are helpful and they also sell Hers chips to go with the pizza.

Omg the food here is great.....we drove 30mins and it was worth the drive!!!! I had shrimp and grits and my boyfriend had biscuits and gravy.....both two great dishes....don't leave without trying the beignets....will be back next Sunday!!!!

Never in my entire life have I ever felt so unwelcome (oh and it's Mothers Day by the way) First, when my Mom went to the hostess stand she didn't even ask how many would be sitting she just assumed it was my mom and myself excluding my dad who was standing right behind me. My mom also complimented her on her headband and the woman completely ignored her. The hostess then walks us to the table and there were about 3-4 other employees just standing in the way, not moving to the side for our convenience. It took probably 15 mins just to get our waiter to the table, and they weren't short staffed because I could count a good amount of employees (reminder it's an airport restaurant, so it's not that big). It then took another 10-15 mins just to get our drinks and after that it took a good while for them to bring my mom and dads food. I didn't eat because I work in customer service and I was just so displeased with how the hostess greeted or I should say lack there of plus the unfriendliness of the other employees. None of the employees smiled they all looked and acted as if they didn't even want to be there. This location has absolutely no customer service and I will never be eating at an O'Charleys again because of my traumatizing experience. I also could tell we weren't the only customers annoyed. Like I said earlier, I work in customer service and I don't like to complain, but this place had zero customer service. I wouldn't even rate them 1 star.

First off, dat dog is the best drunk food. Actually best food normally. 

We had a little wait bc it was a busy Friday night but Jake (the bartender) was awesome and took care of us. Made it a great experience. LOVE THIS PLACE!

Fantastic and rotating selection of beers. A must-go for beer aficionados. Pretzels have been talked to death and for good reason. They are damn good. Frankly, all of the food is pretty darn good considering it's basically a big bar. The $3 monday pint night is a fantastic deal. Only real downside is the 3-beer per night limit if you're working towards a plate.

The chicken was just some regular ol chicken with some cayenne pepper on it nothing special! KFC has better hot chicken... this place is no where near the same level as Hattie bs or princes... not even close.... however....the catfish place is the bomb! The best I've had anywhere around here. They would make it helens catfish and chicken... make the fish the focus because it was 5stars the chicken was below average st best.

Best pizza in town.  And I'm talking about the gluten free version, which is a big deal for me.  Really good gluten free pizza.  Got extra cheese and pepperoni.  And went back the next day for a repeat.
Awesome outdoor atmosphere, helpful service, and fast food delivery. Good size portions!! Try the slow roasted mojo pork plate with rice beans and maduros, yum

Beware they do not install or service Sumner County, even though they advise "Middle TN". 
Went into showroom & got written estimate with added trip charge because we live in White House. I had no problem with that but when I called to setup installation I was then told I was out of service area. There solutions was to buy Fireplace logs from them & have another Company do installation. I will not buy logs from them if they will not install the product they sell.

I basing this review on a delivery type order.

My first interaction is with a female on the phone taking my order.  There is a notable strong language barrier.  I'm not always understanding what she is saying; however, she seems to understand me perfectly.  So the ordering process was slightly difficult, however everything was delivered correctly.  On completing the order, I was given a 45 minute time frame for the food to arrive.  I must say, they were quick, the arrival of my lunch was only 20 min.

Today I ordered the fried dumplings, and a lunch special of general tso's chicken.  The dumplings were very good.  They have one side fried, and just a light brown color with a nice crispy texture.  The filling in the dumplings was very tasty, I'm unsure of what they are filled with, and I didn't ask.  It is a meat product of some type and delicious.  They are delivered with a brown watery type dipping sauce.  This is also very good, slightly salty, with a tangy finish, as well as a hint of onion.  The lunch special size was plenty of food, there is at least enough for 2 meals.  It was very hot on arrival, so hot that I was able to burn my tongue attempting to eat it.  It the general tso's chicken served with fried rice, and an egg roll.  The fried rice is cooked perfectly.  The vegetables in the fried rice taste quite fresh as well.  I have not yet tried the egg roll, however after experiencing the other foods, I'm sure I will like it.  

I must say this is one of the better Chinese type restaurants I have ordered from.  I'm sure I will order again from them.

I adore Itty Bitty! Their hours are sometimes confusing (and change) but it's worth calling to see if they're open! My favorite by far is their chicken salad sandwich -- which I don't even *like* from anywhere but Itty Bitty! Their desserts are also fabulous!

Came in for the first time with a couple of girlfriends for Saturday brunch. This place is so cute! I'm surprised it has taken me this long to make it in. I had the West Coast Turkey sandwich (roasted turkey, bacon, avocado, alfalfa sprouts, field greens, tomato and basil mayo on whole grain). This was BOMB and the ingredients were super fresh. The sandwich came with house-made potato chips which were just OK, I can do without next time.
Oh my this place has the best smoked salmon crepe it is amazing, so delicious, couldn't try any of the dessert crepes most of them had bananas or strawberries which I am highly allergic to

Definitely the local watering hole go-to spot. Great wings (I recommend the hot wings- it's more of a dry rub than a bbq baste, which makes them very tolerable) great drinks (get yourself a Bushwacker or HotTottie) and always great service. Particularly fun in the rainy season as they have a covered back deck and all sorts of sports coverage. Located in the one and only, Sylvan Park! #theplacetobe

Do not eat here, it is filthy, the food is terrible.  I am easy going, but this place pushed me to write a review because it is literally the worst restaurant I have ever eaten in.  The service, management (ran out of more than one food and drink item), and food were all terrible.  The waiter was very nice, but should seek another profession.   All the one star reviews hit the nail on the head, they are all accurate right up to the ridiculous location of the bathroom.  The crawfish were terrible, I have had them before and they were my newest favorite food, but Montrel's Bistro took care of that, they were mealy and discolored and I now hear that they should not have even had them as they are supposed to be out of season.  That explains it, they definitely seemed to be frozen or old.  I repeat again...Do not eat here.

One reviewer had it very right, this is a prime example of how not to run a restaurant.

Such a lovely and kind staff! Don't really feel the need to make an appointment (because yes I'm that person) and they always squeeze me in. The manager Emily is so sweet and patient. Their gel manicures are quick and professional. Definitely recommend if you need a quick changeover from a friendly face.

Food was OK, but the wait was super long, even with reservations.  We had a large party and reservations a week in advance, yet they seated us 1 hour late.  The food took a very long time to arrive.  Several people had to leave before the food arrived due to other appointments; complicating matters.  There are better Mexican restaurants with better service in Tucson

This place is so pretty, classy, and modern. Beautiful bar in the center, relatively low romantic lighting, and not too loud. Service was good and food/drinks were great.

For drinks, I love the Autumn leaves-a fresh light take on fall flavors-not too sweet or strong. Didn't love the passion fruit Negroni-was very bitter. 

For food, our favorites were the chopped salad (like a hearty pizza flavored salad!), meatballs (came with 3 large meatballs, super flavorful), veal saltimboca (yummy salty thinly sliced and fried veal with some perfect simple garlic butter spaghetti), and ricotta gnocchi (perfect little gnocchi puffs with a light creamy sauce). The potatoes were crispy and yummy but would have been even better if cut smaller. The acorn squash was pretty sweet-not bad by any means but not really my jam.

Overall, we really enjoyed this place. Perfect for a date night, girls night, or a slightly pricy "just because" :)
Frito Pie (with jalapeños) and Pumpkin Pie Concrete.  Nuff said!  Fast and friendly service too.

Excellent experience tonight. Nick the bartender was so much fun and provided great service. Then there was the food. Fantastic. I had the pork tenderloin masala and my wife had the Cubano sandwich both of whom were fantastic. Definitely coming back.
I've eaten here a few times and it's always what I expect, average diner food.  Never had a bad meal and service is always good.  The Awful Awful burger is decent.  The chef salad is huge!
Amazing service. Very friendly staff including the chef who explained the dish really well. The poke is authentic. The fish is marinated. Ahi shoyu is really good. The dessert is great too.

May 15, 2016 Sunday - 12 Noon for Lunch
Two Adults

Atmosphere - 5 stars
Food - 4 stars
Service - 4 stars 

Background - I am back because it is Reno's Craft Beer with Drake's being offered up.

Atmosphere - The place has been opened for a few years now and it has more character than when I first went.  Pictures of their customers cover the walls now.  Still lots of TVs for your sports games.

Food
  Drink - The reason I came.  I had a Drake's Hopocalypse Green Label which is a double IPA.  The beer came from a boomer, 22 ounce bottle; I was hoping it was on tap.

  Lunch - I had the Golden Rush Burger, they had me with the avocado.  Nice thick slices of it on the burger.  I had one spot that had too much mustard but that happens.  Is it a $15 burger?  The burger was a half pound burger and had a lot of toppings.  Strange thing is they do not mention the size of the burger in the Steak Burger section but in the Starters section under the Pat LaFrieda Ghost Pepper Sliders.  I picked the tots instead of fries at no additional cost.  I recommend a getting them with garlic parmesan or Cajun spice added, the tots were pretty generic without them.

Service - Lucky Beaver supplied good service.  But the best part was they got two guys from Drake's in that day to talk about their beers.

Future - Their burgers were really good, I could see coming back for another burger.  My wife at the sliders and heat was intense.

This evening was the second time in as many months that I have had very substandard service. I am not sure what has happened at this location during this last year... but it has not been good. 
On a previous occasion after a negative experience I emailed their corporate offices (which are actually local) and  have never gotten a response. 
This evening, it was just very, very apparent that my server did NOT want to be at work... (or perhaps this demeanor is just her MO all of the time, not sure). I FINALLY got a straw toward the END of my meal... I just do not get servers who know they rely on gratuity to survive, having a bad attitude that shows to the patron. Geeze....sorry you are having a bad day lady... but don't bring it to my table.
The entire staff has really gone downhill this last year. 
On a positive note...the day time hostess (whose name I cannot recall) IS THE ABSOLUTE SWEETEST PERSON EVER!!! She needs a promotion or raise Shoney's.

sad to say, celebrated my 29th bday here. okay, it wasn't that bad but didn't have too many choices since we just got in to tucson and the choices we saw were chilli's, macaroni grill, or here. since there aren't too many claim jumper's in the bay area (now one open in fremont - soon to review) decided to check it out. thought it'd be a massive wait but we got seated right away! it was a small gathering with just me, the hubby, and bro (parents were still working) with guests of honor...COUNTRY FRIED CHICKEN, RIB AND CHICKEN COMBO, GOLD RUSH CHICKEN, WEDGE SALADS, and MOZZARELLA STICKS. as most know, the portions are HUGE!!! still, like heffers, we finished it all. all was decent, one of the better chain restaurants. couldn't leave w/ out my free birthday dessert of the RED VELVET CUPCAKE. the cupcake could have tasted better but the side of molten bourbon chocolate sauce was good enough to drink! oh wait, i did....straight to my badunk-a-dunk-dunk!

I love this place!!! I love that they sell pizza by the slice. Pizza is getting so expensive these days. It's nice to be able to buy just a few slices. The pizza is always great and I love sicilian Wednesdays.

I found myself in Franklin for work in the evening hours. I was hungry after having skipped lunch. I got on Yelp and looked for nearby restaurants. Saw this place and thought I should try. I am well pleased.  

I went in and ordered. It's small on the inside. More catered towards take out. You order your choice of pasta and your choice of sauce and whether or not you want meat. I chose Penne, with Cajun sauce and grilled chicken. It took him about 10-15 minutes to make. I assume it's because it's made fresh. 

They have a selection of salads, ice cream and desserts too. But I just got the pasta. Forgot to get a drink. Oops. 

When it did come out, it came out in a take out plastic bowl. (More catered towards takeout) 

Chicken was tender and moist. The pasta was fresh. The sauce was excellent and peppery. There were onions and bell peppers too. I cleaned my plate.  I want to try all the other sauces now!

Edit: 15/12/15 - 

They don't have water on tap to drink. Only bottles. Plus side, it's only a dollar. But I like to drink so I typically drink more than 500ml 

Also, be sure and bring headphones if you're dining in. They were playing awful county music inside. The food makes up for it though.

Let me tell you RUN far away and spend your money elsewhere! Terrible food and service. This was literally the worst Italian food we have ever had. All of our pasta dishes were obviously cooked the day before and warmed up in the microwave as they were cold as ice in the middle. The lasagna is mostly cheese and sauce and some paper thin lasagna noodles you can't taste. The chicken livers were mainly just breading...my husband cut into them and a teeny spot in the middle was the meat. The salads tastes worse than Walmart bagged lettuce with nasty Parmesan that obviously came from a plastic container. Nothing here is made fresh. Even the waiter told us they do this so they can get food out faster. The food is WAY OVERPRICED. If you have a Fazolis around go there instead at least they give you hot food that is cooked the same day and has taste at a great price! Oh and the staff were also terrible and rude to customers. Will never be back!
This was a hidden gym after a long day of class. Healthy portions, price right, and friendly staff. My only concern would be parking, where the PPA is unforgiving!

Update for this establishment,  if I could leave 0 stars I would. 

So my coworker went to this restaurant and got a salad. It had a long hair in the lettuce.  We took the salad back and she showed it to the mgr(I guess that's who he was). He looks at the hair and says that's a long hair.  He looked at the dude beside him and says now who's hair could this be that works in the kitchen? We looked at him like wtf. He takes the salad to the and brings it back.  He says this is a expensive salad you're having us remake and the hair doesn't match anyone in the kitchen. Ummmm what sir??? She told him it was a expensive salad when I bought it. I'm pretty sure that's not good business.  He had an attitude about it and didn't even offer any compensation or apology. 



Tried for the first time today and I'm a little disappointed.  I decided on the Fenwicks basic. The house turkey chorizo left a lot to be desired(no seasoning at all) and the house potatoes were ok, not the best . The biscuit and eggs were the best part of the meal. You win some, you loose some and today I lost with this one.

We tried Pennsylvania 6 for dinner about two weeks after they opened.  They have a nice bar area inside and the food was great. We got the bone marrow (which was one of the best I have had) for an appetizer, and the hanger steak and lobster roll for dinner. Both were very very good. One of the best meals I have had lately.
Uneven swirly spotty spray tan (by hand, not machine). For $45, I expect more and have had much better.

Wife and I have come a few times and we have had a good meal each time. I am still not a fan of most of the Mexican food in TN, as I am used to the Mexican I had from California, but when I am wanting it, this is the only place I have found that does justice to Mexican food, with a great taste, and good quality. I have had the rolled tacos, burritos, tamales, and enchiladas and I have liked them all. If I could have one thing, I would like it with carna asada instead of just ground beef. That's the one main difference I have seen that differentiates California style Mexican from TN style.
It a lovely place and management was very nice but not handicap friendly which is why I never be back great location close to the street car line

Best brewery we visited in Nashville, based on the variety of the beer selection.  We have seen Yazoo beers on draft throughout the South, so were not especially motivated to check out the brewery while we were in town.  But oddly (I mean, this was really strange to us), Yazoo is the ONLY brewery in town open before 4pm on a Friday.  We needed a Friday afternoon activity, so we stopped in.  

We got super lucky because Yazoo was having an anniversary party, so drafts were incredibly cheap and there was a festive atmosphere, but even at full price, this would have been our favorite stop.  To me, the point in visiting the source is to try beers you can't normally find.  Yazoo totally delivers by having some special stuff on tap, including a couple of different wild and sour beers, at least two different IPA's and a gose.  

Seating inside is ample and comfortable, kind of middle of the spectrum in terms of breweries that run from super sleek/restaurant-like to garage/warehouse-like.  That patio was a bit small, which for this city is a bummer since weather is nice for so much of the year.  But Yazoo is definitely worth a stop!

I was honestly skeptical looking online if I'd enjoy the food.. but the atmosphere, food, and service was amazing. 

Those crab cakes I could inhale like 20 lol will definitely be returning !

Alpha Bakery is a great little place.
