We always stop there on Fridays to grab a loaf of challah for Shabbat.  Great challah for sure with or without raisins.  They also never seem to run out, which is also a plus.

I have also tried and enjoyed their Fan Bread, which is essentially like a giant loaf of croissant, glazed or unglazed.  My wife forbid me from bringing them home anymore (although it is amazing warmed with  some plugra butter and home-made strawberry freezer jam).  They also have a great sourdough loaf as well.

My main regret and the reason I would not rate them higher is their hours of operation.  They close at 6PM during the week, and a few times I have showed up with 5-10 minutes to spare and they are already shut tight.  It can be a challenge for people with real jobs to make it there before they close.  Additionally, they require a $5 minimum purchase to use a credit card, which violates all major credit card processing agreements.  Other than that, a great place.

I came here a while ago when my friends and I were in town for Jazz Fest. I keep recommending Bacchanal to friends who are visiting New Orleans, so I felt like it was time to finally yelp about it. Anyway, this was by far my favorite place to hang out and drink in NOLA. It feels like someone's backyard--strung with lights and boasting a collection of mismatched chairs and tables. On the weekends, they tend to have awesome live bands. My friends and I came hungry and bought a bunch of delicious cheeses out of their small, yet fully-stocked fridge and a couple bottles of red wine. We ordered some bread to go with our cheese and wine and had a perfect light meal. Their wine and cheese selection is divine, and I will definitely be back the next time I'm in town!

This food truck was parked outside of Dragoon this past weekend, we tried the beef arepas, the rice, and the plantains - everything was delicious and went down very smoothly with a beer!  The yellow rice was full of flavor, the plantains were different than any I've had before, they were mushy, but very good!  The arepa was packed full of beef and one was very filling!  Friendly owners, and food came out fast!  I'm so glad they were there because I was starving!

So Monicals's is far from my fave but the person I was with absolutely loves it. *shrug*

Their thin crust pizza is popular. I got pepperoni and mushroom. It was okayyy. I also got the garlic bread and it hit the spot but was nothing to write home about, esp for the $6 cost. 

This location has a large back room so that's great for folks who have a large event to host and want a room to rent out. 

Service was great. No wait on a Sunday and the server was very nice and attentive. 

Overall- it's ok. It's not bad but I won't seek it out of my own volition.

I went here with a group of 4 last Friday and I had one of the best dining experiences I've ever had. Everyone in my party did the tasting menu and I'd highly recommend it to meat eaters, vegetarians, and vegans alike. As a vegan myself, I'm so used to steering clear of tasting menus at "normal" restaurants, but I was pleased to find out how knowledgeable and accommodating our server was when it came to dietary restrictions!

Vegan highlights: hummous, baba ganough, muhammara, taboulé, battata harra, grilled eggplant, sorbet. 

I'm excited to come here again. Suraya is amazing!

Kim wanted some oysters before we left the quarter on Saturday night. So we went to Acme and there was a line and there was a line across the street at Felix's as well. That's when we decided to do the Bourbon House. No line there should have been a warning. The oysters were small and not cheap ($17 for a dozen) but that wasn't the worst part by any means. This is supposed to be a nice restaurant and the service SUCKED. We sat at the oyster bar and the first server was disinterested and lame. We had to ask for menus and then for water and then for our food and then for our napkins and then remind him we were waiting for drinks. The other server had no clue who at the bar ordered what and so every time he brought out an order he first asked us if we had ordered it. Finally when, after much hassle, i was able to get the bill, I noticed I had been charged $15 for my shot of Makers Mark 46 as opposed to the $10 it was supposed to cost. I asked Drew (the second server) about the cost difference and he said, "Oh, all of our shots are served in a complimentary shot glass. If you don't want it, you can go to the host station and turn it for the $5." WTF is that!! What sort of stupid slimy move is that when that's not mentioned anywhere on the menu or by the server? They just obviously hope customers don't check their bill - which most probably don't - so they can scrape another $5 off each one. It's too bad that that place carries the Dickie Brennan name and it's too bad that with so many good places to get oysters in the Quarter, we wasted $50 at that one. If you do end up going there even after reading this review, Do Not sit at the oyster bar and make sure to check your bill before paying!

Some of the best beers I've ever had. Multiple new releases every week, and the most amazing collection of sours I've ever encountered. Hatfield has a lot more walk in than Pottstown but everything here is amazing!
The smoojies are amazing!!!

This place is a mess. Service is terrible; waitress didn't have a clue what to do. Drink from bar was bad and had to be returned. They were out of french fries. No refill on water. They said kitchen was being "slammed," but the place was less than half full. The person pointed out to me as the owner walked around inside seemingly clueless of how bad an experience her customers were having. Too many better places to eat in this area. It's a shame too because the outdoor seating is not bad.
This a great place.  They have food, pool, darts and the best prices in town.  Jager Bombs are $4. Nobody can bet that! Lots of TVs if you love sports and a friendly crowd. I love it here.
I hadn't eaten in 23 hours and got a slinger.  It was everything I could have wanted.  Came out quick, was warm, place was quiet inside.  Just what I needed
If there was a half star or zero they'd get it! Most rude pharmacist I've ever encountered! Dave. I would drive out of my way to never encounter him again! RUDE! RUDE! RUDE!

I was going to go on and on but basically everything that was said below is still true.

Also I was charged an upgrade for an item.  However, it was posted.

Food is good service is not.

I hope it improves.

So on March 27, 2018, I tried again.  After 20 minutes and only 3 customers ahead of me I left.  Still completely unorganized.

What a shame I love their food, but it is such an investment in time and frustration its not worth it to me.

The name Royal Sonesta should give you a hint

This is our second time.  each visit is a pleasure 

The facility is surprisingly cared for with excellent service and management

The concierge was hard-working and always available -- our group made several changes with dinner reservations one night and he did not get flustered

Location location location --  you cannot beat a Bourbon Street location

In side you are in a tranquil and peaceful environment --  outside your are in the noisiest part of the French quarter --- they are geniuses for insulation
I very much enjoyed visiting this market. Great products, and the donuts in the back are to die for. Will be back!

Worst experience ever!  On October 11, 2017 I rented a car from Budget at Philadelphia airport when I went to see my dad in the hospital.  When I arrived the shuttle bus was packed with people.   I ran off the bus and was fourth in line.  There were two regular customer service reps and one for their Fastbreak clients. 

When the one rep was finished with her customer she left.  The other rep was having a problem with a customer's license and went in the back to get the manager.   He came out.   The line now had over 15 people inline and growing.   I thought for sure the manager would notice and get help or at least jump in there himself.  But NO he went back behind the wall to his office.   The Fastbreak rep then disappeared.   So now there was only one rep to handle all the people in line.   It was now over 40 minutes.  So I called the number I found for that location to see if I could reach the manager.   I could hear it ringing in the back office.   It rang for over 10 minutes.  No one picked up the phone. Finally the second rep returned from the back.  She had apparently gone on lunch break since she was still chewing something when she returned.   My wait was almost an hour before I had my car.   I can't image how long those at the back of the line had to wait.  Then when they brought my car around, the guy that brought didn't even check to make sure it was mine.  He just walked away. 

BUT IT GETS WORSE.........My return flight was at 6am on October 17, 2017.  So we were at Budget with the car around 4:30 am.   We pulled up and there was no rep to check in the car.   We looked around.  One car was running another had its lights on but there was no one around.   So we walked to the building.  A man was waiting there for a rep and had been waiting for about 10 - 15 minutes.  He said he saw no one.   So I decided to check in the back, where I had seen the manger go when I picked up the car.   I called down the hallway but got no answer.  I slowly walked down the hall calling out "Hello is anyone here?"  Finally at the end of the hall there was a young woman sitting at a table eating chips.   When she saw me she told me customers were not allowed and I needed to get out of there. 
I told her we were trying to drop off our car.  She told me, in a very nasty tone, to wait in the front because she was on break.  I asked her name and she replied "My name is Get Out Of Here." I told her I was concerned because I wanted to get to my flight.  She became angry and told me just to get out.   She said I could leave the key in the car and take the Avis shuttle because that was what they do early in the morning.   I said it would be nice if there was a sign with those instructions.  She just told me I did not have to be sarcastic and again told me to leave.  She was VERY NASTY and refused to give me her name.  ... and kept eating her chips. 

So we left the key in the car and walked to Avis to catch the shuttle.  I advised the other man waiting to do the same.   I prayed that no one pulled in behind my rental and hit the car.  I did not want to be blamed for that.   

READ THIS TOO:  

When I got home I received a survey request.   I gladly completed it and detailed my experience.  To my surprise I received an email from Theresa Evans stating she was sorry I had a bad experience and would like to speak to me about my experience.   I replied OK and sent my phone number.   When I did not hear from her, I emailed her again from a different email (thinking maybe the first one went to junk).  Again, I told her to contact me and gave my phone number.   Well no surprise...... She NEVER contacted me.   So much for being sorry.   I bet she told her boss she responded to me but I did not respond to her.   

It was terrible service from start to finish!   This was not the first bad experience with Budget (I had a bad one in Newark, NJ earlier this year) but PHL was definitely the worst.  I will NEVER rent from Budget again.   I will pay more for a rental so that I know I will get good service.  I guess you get what you pay for.

Awesome place to eat breakfast and/or lunch.  Owner was very attentive and friendly...The food was to die for.  More than enough on your plates to keep you coming back for more.  The downside...The wait for breakfast was horrendous.  They really need to look at their utilization of space.  Over fifty percent of the restaurant was dead space that could be used to seat patrons.  While we were waiting, there were at least 5 two tops that either left that had been waiting or came in and turned around and walked out and that was just in 25 minutes.  Do the math, $75x365 is about $28000.  Does it happen every day, probably not but it shouldn't happen at all when you've got great food, great staff, and down to earth prices.  Hopefully next time in town they will have things figured out as we will definitely be back.

Glad to have a local place in brewerytown that serves awesome beer. I tried every beer that wasn't an IPA, all of which were interesting and complex. Not they type of beer you can get at any bar.The food is simple, fresh, and delicious. Any service issues others have experienced might be because the Brewers themselves run the place, I'm assuming until they can afford to hire more staff. With that being said it probably is a little overwhelming especially if they haven't done customer service in the past. Highly recommend!

Excellent craft brew menu from local vendors. Food was wonderful, I had a French dip on a burger,  it was sensational. Loved the large onion rings also. Patio seating was nice as the road wasn't very busy with trafgic.

Pizza was okay and salad was good. Ordered delivery and pizza was not hot, barely warm at best. Sad since they were less than 3 miles from my location. In addition, I gave the driver the only cash I had as I put tip on my card and they called me before delivery and their system was not working correctly. They said cash was best and when I gave it to driver, he opened it and said something about why didn't I put it on card. I explained they called and he put the cash in his pocket and then said write more in the receipt and he would have it added. I was a little shocked at the way he handled and hope they don't charge my card more. I also asked for plates etc and the girl taking my order said okay they would send some and then when I asked the driver, he said no and they don't do that. He then got in and just drove away in front of me. I would not recommend as one of the better places but we wanted something different...I paid for that decision. I will not order again.

Always has the best queso!!!! Whenever we have party's I stop by her bro grab a large order of chips, salsa, and home made queso. It's so creamy and you can obviously tell it's fresh and made with real goat cheese.

I always get get the Arroz con pollo. Uses the same amazing queso, so you know it's always going to be delicious! 

Service is super faster! I think the most I have ever waited is maybe 10 minutes for our food! 

This place is so good it got to a point we were going probably once a week. Very good authentic Mexican food. They did just recently make menus and maybe ownership changes. Which means some favorite were taken off an prices went up about a dollar. But still very good that they make it well worth it!
Usually really good, sometimes over done for my liking, overall an awesome calzone place with a chill staff

Wow! Green Valley Locksmith got me out of a jam!  I'm very impressed with the service John provided. I looked up a local locksmith using Yelp and within 15 minutes he was at my door! It's nice to know there are still small businesses that believe in providing great customer service! I highly recommend calling and utilizing this company. You wont be disappointed!
Everyone here is so nice! They remember you months later and it's evident they truly care about the longevity of your teeth!

5/5 if you want a great date night or social gathering hang out spot! 

The ambiance of this venue is perfect for a night out to enjoy some delicious Italian. If you are planning on taking a date there, I would recommend you sitting outside or getting a reservation a little later in the evening as the rush our can get a little loud. 

So far, my favorite dishes have been their baked ziti, carbonara, and if you get there for their happy hour, their burger! 

The staff is friendly and there TVs inside to watch any football game, so if you want an excuse to come out, this is it!

Worst dealer experience I ever had! I put a $2500 deposit to secure a car while I arranged a flight from Florida. I liaised with the salesperson, Stephen, advising him of my flight time and assuring him I had a cashiers check. When I arrived at the Maple Shade dealership, the car had not been prepared at all. It was disgustingly dirty inside and out, the key fob needed a new battery and didn't work, there was a warning light saying it needed servicing, the roof wouldn't open. They had this car for weeks and offered it for sale in appalling condition. I am still waiting for my refund. Wasted time and cost of flights.

If you can get past the noisy dining room, this is a fabulous dining experience.  (I don't think  there are any quiet restaurants in NOLA.)  But the food is exceptional.  We followed the referrals of a couple sitting next to us for both appetizers and entrees.  The fried oysters and white asparagus soup were delicious.  Couldn't decide which was better among the two entrees we ordered, the scallops or the cochon (pork)  Both were excellent.If you bring your own wine, there is no corkage charge for the first bottle.  The servers were all very pleasant and capable.   Definitely a place to return to next year.

A friend of mine recommended this place when I told him I was going to Tucson and after walking by and seeing how cute it was I knew we had to try it! We sat outside even though it was a little chilly, the propane heater really helped. The service was great. The outdoor seating area was too great to pass up and the food was fantastic!!
The texture of the noodles was perfect and the tomato broth on the seafood dish was delicious!  I'm already craving it!

Just all around bad experience... First, the NoWait app tells us it will be 45 minutes. Then we get to the restaurant after 25 minutes drive and wait for almost an hour to get a table. They did send a text that the table is ready after 20 minutes or so, but then proceeded to tell us that was a mistake. Anyway, we finally get a table and the place is so loud that you cannot hear yourself think... Then the food... Unacceptable. My burger was cold, fries - soggy, potato skins were swimming in grease, my wife's pasta was hot, but absolutely lacking any flavor... And the most disappointing was my bloody mary - a watery, tasteless concoction that did not appear to have any alcohol in it... We had a long workday, and just did not want to start an argument. But we will never set foot into this place ever again

This place is kind of lowkey, right next to a gas station. They only have outside seating and the inside is to order. The environment is really chill. I have ordered from here before, it was a banh mi and it tasted like heaven. This time I ordered banh mi thit nuong (grilled pork) with egg and crab rangoon. Both were 10/10. The egg really added to the sandwich. The crab rangoon had imitation crab in it and the filling was amazing. Some places do not make their crab rangoon good, but this is one of the places that do. Their sweet chili sauce was a 10/10 too. Definitely recommend eating here.

This has become my go-to spot for mani / pedi's. I have been 4 times and usually get one or the other. My last trip was on a Sunday afternoon for a mani. 

When I walked in, my heart sank as there were 4 people ahead of me--including 2 tweens choosing their glitter polish. I chose to sign in and wait it out. I started to become frustrated after 15 min. but one of the staff came to get the 2 girls and said it would only be a few more minutes. I only had about an hour as I'd left my 16-month old with a babysitter! Waaaah! 

I ended up waiting a total of 25 minutes for a 15-20 min service. It was worth it. The staff member who did mine was efficient, kind, and competent. I found myself wishing I had time for a pedi, too! 

The atmosphere at Excursion is nicer than most strip mall salons--there's a little waterfall, warm, earth tones, and several TV's with volumes set to low. They also offer bottled water or wine. (It would be nice if they gave it to you while you were waiting!) It doesn't have the awful chemical smell that others have either.

I paid $15 plus tip for the mani. A pedi is $30. If you do both, it's $40. I left there happy with my nails which are just barely beginning to chip 4 days later.

We came here for dinner. The service is the best, they are very friendly and helpful, gave us good advise when we could not choose which one to order because there are so many awesome option. The server also gave us tips to keep guacamole fresh by squeezed lemon on top. There was a big portion for every serving. I will definitely come back again.
Gnocchi was amazing! Crab cakes are huge with all crab filling! Size of baseballs. Service was great! Calamari was the best I've ever had! I will definitely be returning again soon!

Since I was going to be at the convention center for 4 days, I knew one of my meals had to be at Cochon Butcher given all its awesome Yelp reviews. It's literally a 5-minute walk, making it a very convenient lunch. Unfortunately, everybody else attending the conference knew this as well so the line was quite long although it moved quickly. However, it was so crowded that there was no place to sit. You pretty much had to fight for a table so I decided to just take my sandwich to go. I ended up ordering the muffaletta ($12) and it was just okay. I know most of the Yelp reviews raved about how good it is, but there was just so much grease that it just wasn't that enjoyable after awhile. The only break from the grease is the olive salad, but there was really little in my sandwich. I think a bit more would've helped. I did enjoy the bread though. It was fresh and perfectly toasted.

I think I may have ordered the wrong type of sandwich for my taste. I like more fresh ingredients versus just a bunch of cured meats so that's partly my fault, but I have no problem eating a good old pastrami sandwich so it's not like I don't enjoy meaty sandwiches! Anyways, I have to review based on my experience and it was just mediocre so 3 stars it is.

Nothing to write home about. My husband and I went for lunch expecting great things as they are typically busy over the lunch hour. It was obvious that everything was made from scratch, but every dish just seemed to be lacking flavor. I had the shrimp soup and one shrimp taco. My husband had two carnitas tacos and two carnitas gorditas with a rice water. The shrimp soup was fine; a little spicy (which was the best part). The shrimp taco was bland, and the carnitas was bland as well. The rice water had a slightly grainy texture (which is normal), but the flavor was awesome. I had never tried it before, and it reminded me of chai.

All in all, the food was fine, but not good enough for us to return.

Monday night at Charley's for my daughters birthday. I had heard good things about this place and they did not disappoint. Great steaks, great apps and sides, particularly the calamari and lobster Mac and cheese. Truly worth the visit and expense for special occasions. Walked out tip and all,no dessert or alcohol for 4 people under $260. Not bad for a great experience. Place needs a facelift but I'm not eating the wood paneling that it has ubiquitously throughout. To dark and dingy inside and out. Thanks Willie for your exceptional service.

First visit to this busy taco place. When you walk up and there is a massive line..it's a good sign. The fish was fresh, the carne asada taco was seasoned well, hot sauce on point. Even with the long line, it moved fast and food came out fast as well. I highly recommended this place for tacos and fish n chips!

This was a great place to stop with friends and coworkers after work. Service is excellent and the menu is perfect and manageable. I'm pretty sure we've tried everything on the food and drink menu.  It's a can't miss kind of spot and only goes wrong when you fall in love with a particular dish and discover that they rotate things out.  Please bring back the smoked ricotta.
Wonderful breakfast! I had the Chicken & Waffles (so good!) Others in the party really enjoyed the hash brown casserole and omeletes. The biscuits and jam are 5 star!!

I came in on a Thursday evening and sat at the bar for a drink and some appetizers with a few friends. There was only one bartender available most of the night to serve the bar guests and all the seated guests so we waiting at least 20 minutes to get her attention and order and some appetizers. Although frustrating, we understood she was really busy. The next day I checked my credit card statement and I was charged $81 more than I should have been. I called and was told the error was fixed in their system and will post to my account for the correct amount. This was also very frustrating. 

This was my first time here and was really excited for the opening of a Harvest in Newtown which is close to home. Really disappointing first impression. Apps were pretty good, it's a shame my experience was so crappy.

I wish I could give this place 0 stars. And although the food is horrible, flavorless, and completely falsely advertised as "healthy" and "organic," this rating is because the owner is one of the worst businessmen I have ever had the misfortune of dealing with. A few months back, Bryn Davis "hired" a few friends of mine to work on various programs. After weeks of promising these individuals compensation, he never followed through. He also buys much of his fruit from Sam's Club, which I can pretty much guarantee is not organic. He cares very little about the quality of his food. Instead, he will cut all corners to afford cheap product but will continue to claim that it's all natural or all healthy. 

Bryn has been advertising corporate events and a bryn and dane's food truck. The truck is a piece if junk that can barely even make it down the road without harming someone. Anyone who has seen this truck knows what I'm talking about. These corporate events are a complete and utter joke and a harm to people on the road. I can't even imagine what the back of the kitchen looks like. 

Back to the food - smoothies are okay. I got extremely sick from the mo green smoothie once, and I'm pretty sure that's because there were ingredients in the smoothie that weren't listed, but most of the time they are decent. The food, on the other hand, is basically a bunch of flavorless mush with an expensive price. Basically - DONT GO TO THIS PLACE -  TRUST ME. you will be unbelievably disappointed. 

As for Bryn Davis, here's some business advice: spend less time posing in pictures with celebrities, trying to be famous, and holding bogus "healthy" events just for an excuse to drink in public. And, spend more time focusing on managing a business that actually provides "healthy fast food."

Omg! How have I not reviewed Verti market yet!?!?

I love this place it's one of my favorite places in New Orleans! If it had seating and a bar it would be foodie heaven! 

The menu is insane! Breakfast, lunch, dinner, cake! All available 24/7! 
You want crabcakes and french toast for breakfast? Got it! A salad at 4 am! Scalloped potatoes and pie in the middle of the night, that's what they do! 

They are the dream of every pregnant woman, stoner and insomniac foodie! 
Cash only though!

Everything started okay with check in and then the the X-rays but then it went down hill quickly from there. The dentist spent only a couple of minutes with me and didn't really examine my mouth or even talk to me much. After that the hygienist came in and all of a sudden my wife and I required expensive treatments. I really felt as though we were being hustled almost like I was at a shady used car lot. We are new to the area and will have to continue our search for a dental office.

We visit several times a week. Great little spot. Lots of families and kids from the college. Best flavors are Caramel Pretzel (top with heath) and Red Velvet Cupcake (top with sprinkles). Be sure to enter your cell phone number on the pad by the register. 10 visits gets you a free 10oz + they send you coupons via text.

After years of living with hair on the back of my neck that just never made sense to me, I finally did some research on getting rid of it once and for all. I found Callie!! We had a wonderful consultation where she made me feel comfortable about moving forward with laser hair reduction and we got started that day!! Now, it did not tickle and I was grateful having something to hold onto for the initial pain, but it didn't last long and I am one step closer to being able to get that short haircut I have been wanting. Thanks Callie!!!

It is beautiful, but not exactly what I look for in a beach day. There are tons of people around. There is no near by parking, we parked at a hotel garage after getting dropped off ($16). The sand is amazingly soft...but with that comes extremely sandy everything with the slightest wind. Literally all of our stuff and ourselves were covered in sand by the end of the day, not too pleasant. I would definitely come to this area again, but to a more secluded part. There is one public bathroom, but by mid day there was about a 20 min wait for it. So overall could definetly use some improvement, wow am I actually spoiled by the Jersey shore beaches??

I was disappointed with my appointment. The nurse took down my concerns, but only two out of three were talked about with the doctor. When asking for details about a procedure, I was referred to their website. I can Google that, and already read it. I wanted details from the doctor. This was a second opinion. I won't go back to this practice. While it wasn't horrible, it was nothing compared to the great practice that I went to for my first opinion. I think this would be a fine place to go for very every day things.

OMG!! Listen I was born braised  in the Deep South of Georgia. This place is a newly found jewel of Nevada! This is as Southern as it gets and has become my family's newest resturant we can't get enough of! The black eyed peas are the best! Everything at this place is the best of Southern Real Cooking! They even have kool aid! You want a great taste of the south come here! It takes some time to get your order but it is so worth it. 
I order the fried chicken gizzards and black eyed peas... my husband gets country fried steak, collard greens and beans n rice. Plus the southern tea is so yummy! I'm so happy we found this place! Smells like when my great grandmas is cooking in the kitchen . As we wait for dinner on the front porch in the porch swing.. listening to the great great grandparents sharing stories to pass down...

We loved it here. So much fun with a Karaoke. There is an upstairs and downstairs and you will be dancing all night. Saturday nights are the best. Drinks are somewhat reasonably priced. Bartenders are not friendly, but who cares the crowd is great and fun

Several friends and I continued our mini-pub crawl of mixology bars (begun at Franklin Mortgage and Investment Co.) here. Good move!

We parked it at the bar and got the show from Sasha, the bartender, who kept up friendly banter with us even as she concocted a variety of beverages throughout the course of our stay. 

The cocktail menu was fairly extensive, broken down into Prohibition- and Repeal-era drinks, not to mention long lists of bourbons, ryes, and scotches. I ordered an Aviation (a drink I make myself, with my own brandied cherries, but here they do it the right way, all out with Creme de Violette to tint it blue like the sky; Sasha let me take a look at the bottle, perhaps to know that it wasn't some awful curacao!) 
For another friend she created a drink with Art in the Age of Mechanical Reproduction's Root liqueur (which is made with the roots and herbs used in old-fashioned root beer), chocolate bitters, seltzer and orange. 

We also partook of food here: First, duck fat fries (which have been a trend in Chicago, where I live, for at least a year, but I'd never had them; I'd never eaten anything involving duck before this, so now I suppose I have lost my duck fat innocence). These were thick-cut, rich in taste [gratis the duck fat, one presumes], not actually greasy, but definitely better when ordered with the cup of cheese sauce on the side. 

We also got soft pretzel sticks, which would have been fine but not especially remarkable without the mustard sauce (which had a distinct taste of raspberry, to my mind) pooled in the cup underneath them.

Overall, this was a friendly place with fab drinks and great food. I wish it was in my city.

I had a house guest lock himself out of his bedroom while I was 3,000 miles away on the other side of the country.  Several break in strategies were tried, but in the end I needed to find a locksmith after-hours around 9pm at night.  I called around and found other inexpensive "locksmith's" but they seemed shady and I was afraid to let strangers into my home.  I got A&A Dolan's number off of Angie's list, so I felt safer letting them into my home.  It took Brian about 40 minutes total to get to my house and unlock the lock.  (He drove to south Philly from the burbs).  He gave me a good rate and it was well worth the peace of mind.  Although I was frustrated about the lockout situation, at least A&A Dolan made solving the problem stress free.

After a good experience here a year ago, I was sorely disappointed this past weekend. I came on a Friday morning to get my oil changed, and also decided to get my transmission fluid and radiator fluid changed, around $330 worth of services. After the services, I noticed that my oil change light was still yellow, but I thought that might be due to the fact that it was the first time I switched to synthetic oil. I had told the guys that I was getting my oil changed because I was going on a long road trip. Imagine my surprise when my oil change light changed from yellow to red. I pulled over and measured my engine oil level using the stick - I barely had any oil in my engine! Due to this mistake, I had to drive about a hundred miles in the red, something I hate doing due to the risk to the engine. This was a costly and risky mistake that this shop did.

i'm not sure why some establishments feel they can treat their customers poorly just because they have good food?!? I think great food, especially pizza, it's one of my favorites is worth paying extra for, or even going out of the way to purchase. However nothing can overcome rude service. i'm not talking about a mixup or mistake I'm talking about being treated like I was inconveniencing them by wanting to place a order. i've read through the comments here and apparently I'm not the only one who experienced food service within the past few months. Guys, eventually this will catch up to you if you don't correct it.

If it's hot out, and you were not headed over to Hawaii, stop in at ParadICE Shave Ice and cool off.

Wonderful fresh organic fruit flavors!

The Shave Ice Team is happy to make your Shave Ice just the way you want. Just like the old fashion roadside Shave Ice Stands in Hawaii.

Yes, ask your server to include a scoop of the toasted coconut ice cream on the bottom. +=  ;~) 

Take the rest of the week off. You can really enjoy these!

My coconut enzyme has been active. -8~) enjoy!
Great food and great service. Love the atmosphere. Never disappointed when I come here. The yogurt soju is amazing

By far one of the BEST places to have breakfast from Goleta to Carp. Food is fresh, tasty combinations and affordable. Call ahead to get reservations (all the tourists will be there waiting for a table) and request the patio seating. Overall thought: the combination of the beautiful view and delicious food make this place one of the best!

The sushi at Sushi Lovers is more fresh than any place I've been in Reno and is very comparable to the best I've had in Seattle. It literally melts in your mouth!

The staff is very friendly. I went with a regular and didn't have to bother with the menu - I was just given the best they had and it was amazing. There are several unique things about this place including the home made glazes and tempura fried seaweed chips.

This business is very new, but the staff is not. They do an amazing job!
So so good! Casual, relaxed, with a ton of seafood items in the menu. Nice staff and beer on tap. I will go again!

I'm not sure if this was a one-time fluke that was simply a consequence of my less-than-superb luck, but either way I am pretty disappointed. After reading the excellent reviews, and seeing the great prices for their services as well as a perfect location, I was eager to stop by for a wax. I called ahead a few times to try and set up an appointment only to hear the phone ring and ring and go to voicemail. I didn't think much of this figuring they must be with a client, so I stopped in. But, the door was locked. Even the hairstylist of the salon sharing their space was bewildered where the technicians were, as it was well past their open business hour, with no explanation why they were closed. So, I went to Nouvelle and this spa lost my business. Not a very good first impression to say the least, and not sure I will return to give them a second chance seeing as Nouvelle offers the same rates and is much more reliable.

One of the top two food experiences I've had in New Orleans, and I eat out A LOT.  The service is impeccable and the food is exquisite.  As I'm sure many others have also said, try the foie gras three ways.

I switched to this dry cleaner last year and I  am truly satisfied with their service. The staff is friendly and my clothes are always ready on time. There are other dry cleaners that are closer to my home but I make the additional commute because I know my clothes are guaranteed to be handled with care here.

I took my wedding gown here to get steamed before my Big Day. I was a bit nervous leaving my gown at the shop because it was so expensive. However, the shop owner did a beautiful job. Do not hesitate having a wedding gown steamed at this dry cleaners.

The owner is wonderful. He remembers his customers and is always so positive! So not only did I get to have amazing service, but the food was excellent too. 

I had the yummy pad thai and *Note*: unlike many places in Edmonton, when he says it's spicy, it's actually spicy. Go 0.5 out of 1 chili pepper (mild with a bit of spice) if you're a wuss like me. I'm looking forward to going back and next time it's going to be to for the green curry.

Moving from California to Indianapolis I had a lot of trepidation trusting someone with my hair, I kind of marry my stylist and never stray. Anthony was recommended by my stylist in LA, and I am really thrilled he "got it". Awesome personality, continues his education constantly, and really cares about not only your hair but the whole package. Coming from LA I was in snob mode about the address, forget that, inside the front door there is so much talent by Anthony. Thanks!!!

A family run German style place specializing in schnitzels and similar, though they have quite a large menu and offer a lot of breakfast options through lunch also (came here with some co-workers who swear by always ordering the eggs benedict). They have a daily special and also keep some German beers on tap - yum.

I had the schnitzel special, which turned out to be a pork schnitzel with a mild cheese topping, and you can choose your side - iirc, the options were fries, garlic mash, or spaetzle (fried dumplings). My co-worker who ordered the mash said it was amazing, and I really liked the dumplings. The servings are huge, very few of us could even finish our dishes and had extras left to take away.

The schnitzel itself was a little bland, to be honest; seemed like a little more seasoning or at least salt and pepper would have been an improvement. So, not blown away by the schnitzel, although my companions all enjoyed their orders, but there's a ton of other things to try on their extensive menu. And did I mention the menu includes a rather humorous timeline of the business? We had a lot of laughs reading through the ups and downs of Barb & Ernie.

There IS parking, but it's a very tiny lot, so you may have to find a street nearby.

I find this place to be an over priced olive garden. I couldn't decide what to get so I went with the classic, chicken parmigiana. Since this is an Italian restaurant they should be exceptional at this dish. I stand corrected, chicken was rubbery, sauce had no taste. Not worth the price, go somewhere else.

Food was good but not great. We went there for Taco Tuesday. My wife got the shredded chicken tacos. When she was eating she bit down on a chicken bone so hard she started bleeding inside her mouth enough where blood was coming down the side of her lip. My issue here wasn't the bone I understand that may happen time to time. My issue is we said something to the bartender where we were served and she went to the back to say something to the kitchen staff. YOU WOULD THINK A MANAGER WOULD COME AND CHECK ON MY WIFE AND MAKE SURE SHE WAS OK. That didn't happen and no food was comped or not even a drink which was only one apiece. We do like this place since it's only two blocks from our house however they need to get better management and customer service.
Slow,  unorganized, and bad attitudes. Manager was very rude. The only good things r the location and the food is usually fresh.

I've had them work on a few vehicles over the past few years and they are great. Reasonable, reliable, trustworthy, giving me updates on the progress. I recommend then to anyone. I've had insurance & self-pay jobs, with a rental car and without, with a tow and without. (Yes, I'm a mess with cars.) They had been recommended to me & I'm glad they were.

While I do think the food here is good, they need to get their act together with their take-out orders.  They have so much take out business that they get overwhelmed and behind EVERY TIME we order.  Tonight it took more than an HOUR extra (after the 30 min we were told when we ordered online!)  Definitely will be finding a new place for Chinese carry-out.

He did such a good job and I only needed an ice pack and a couple of regular Tylenol after a double tooth extraction I would never go anywhere else I was Treated with respect  and compassion  surgeons have great skill  state-of-the-art facility extremely clean knowledgeable  friendly staff I had a few bad teeth removed  they were in really bad shape  and I was very nervous as I don't like dentistry in general the procedure went smoothly  the surgical skill that this doctor give to my jaw during the procedure is impressive it was very stable minimally damaged. The gum closure technique used was the best I have ever experienced Considering all been done to it I have to say that I was extremely impressed not to mention that it is the end of the second day and I've only had to take two regular Tylenol for pain that's it unfortunately I've lost many teeth over the years  and I've had several of them removed here as well as I have had others removed at different places prior to finding them  but I would not ever go anywhere else I have had several procedures at this surgical office over the course of many years I have referred family and friends if you're looking for knowledge skill state-of-the-art equipment cleanliness professionalism and intelligent friendly staff this is the place they are very attentive to their patients and took good care of me even in the middle of the night as I had woken up with a severe toothache and the doctor called me immediately back the service is commendable I have also been treated here for a jaw injury as well as trigeminal neuralgia from a brain tumor the procedure went very quickly as well even though I had two extractions I have sent my daughter here for her wisdom teeth as well as my two sons have also had their wisdom teeth removed here as well every visit Was the Same clean trustworthy professional good quality work

Lenny's is a breakfast and lunch restaurant with a NY diner feel. It has been open over 30 years,
and the decor looks original.
From 7 am till 3pm this place is busy. The food
and service are excellent. The waitresses are
friendly, and give good suggestions. 
Breakfast comes with complementary mini
danish. They even give you a bag to take home
what you don't eat. The coffee is excellent.
The breakfast items I've eaten here such as
Eggs Benedict, various omelets, pancakes, bacon and sausage are delicious. For lunch, you must try
one of their deli sandwiches,  burgers, or salads.
The reuben is a must. Their  triple threat sandwiches are for the healthy appetite.
There is plenty of parking, but on the weekends
bring your patience. This place gets packed.

Average food for the young crowd that doesn't know better. Tightly packed on weekends. And Seriously, you can get this food at any respectable dinner or breakfast place anywhere. No oatmeal, no low calorie options, almost everything is served with lots of sweets. Enjoy and Pay=Cash Only.

Ordered 4th street from caviar tonight. Caviar totally messed up, but the manager of 4th street made up for it. He called twice, letting us know he remade the meal THREE TIMES and offered us a comped dessert. 

The matzo ball soup was excellent. It was full of clean flavors, with a healthy dose of dill. I needed a bit of salt, but I love salt so...

The chicken in the pot was huge and delicious. Giant dumplings, matzo balls, carrots, potatoes and chicken were sent to us in a giant glass ball jar. Wonderfully tasty and enough for 3 meals. 

The pastrami rueben was spot on flavor wise and equally enormous.  

Finally the chocolate cake was super rich and tasted like it was made that morning. 

Great service and food. Highly recommend!

You want to love this place. Great location. Fantastic history. And a wonderful wait staff. But after going there multiple times, over a long timeframe, and sampling different menus and dishes, you can't get past the mediocrity of the food. Which in Nashville - packed with some of the country's most amazing restaurants - is a shame. It's not hard to ruin avocado toast, but somehow they managed it, by saying it's on focaccia but really putting it on tasteless wannabe Texas toast. It's not hard to ruin "baked eggs" over grits, but then you get a mess of scrambled eggs. And if you've got only one steak option - at steakhouse prices - make it a better quality cut, and learn to cook it. Medium rare isn't brown in the middle. Just constant sloppiness all around. You might be more forgiving if it was less pricey, but not for what they charge. The best you can say is, the food is hit or miss. Some dishes are OK, most are meh. When you can get a reservation any time on OpenTable, you know people must not be fans. (Scroll through the reviews and you will see similar commentary.) Really hoping they can turn it around, but until things improve, recommend booking elsewhere.

Not liking how Paradise and Panera are merging. They each had their delicious unique items. Im in love with their Fontina Grilled Cheese though! Drive thru service is quicker and friendlier than dine-in service, which is intetesting.

We went there for lunch on our way to the airport. 30 minutes after we placed our order the food had yet to arrive. The manager came over and apologized for the delay and assured us that our food would arrive within 5 minutes (which it did).

When the food arrived the server told us again that the manager was sorry for the delay and comped all three of our meals.  And of course the food was perfectly prepared. Outstanding customer service!!!  Of course I'll be back.

Great place for all your dental needs. Dr. Raissi is very kind, and genuinely funny. Fortunately he doesn't joke during the cleaning so that your teeth can stay intact and your gums unscarred.

Its a new spot too, so I definitely recommend!

,not a sandwich person,
Read some reviews and thought why not,ordered the buckboard bacon melt and it was  great,dont be discouraged when there is a  line,they,are fast,and they bring the food out twice as fast,bought 2 jars of pickles they are deliscious.will be back tomorrow.staff not the friendliest,some are most are not.jerry was nice and helpful.

Cute and unique place in Webster Groves. My husband and I came for lunch and got great food and great service! The Salmon Burger was amazing, I ended up letting my husband have some of mine because he liked it so much! Also recommend their potato salad. Great place with local ingredients and a homey feel
Not bad - not great - Confusing to order - deck is nice - think taco bell on steroids

We waited an hour and a half but the food was worth the wait. We had the raw oysters, the corn and crab bisque and the seafood etouffe. Everything we ate was excellent. It was worth the wait.  I highly recommend it and believe me it was worth the wait. It's not the best service, but again, great food.

I've been coming to this place for the past year. I always try to eat something different, typically the spicy items. The food is always good and the portions are huge for the amount you spend. It's a tiny place but they always have room for my friends and I when we go in.

Hands down my favorite restaurant for comfort food in Indy. Huge fan of the brisket, the Brussels and the Mac n cheese. Great vibes for a chill day with a great outdoor setup. Beer is cold and good! I'm usually there every couple weeks for dinner and always suggest this spot to friends unfamiliar with the restaurant.

A PRICEY, $16.49 BLAND & UNFILLING LUNCH (SEE PIC)
1. The $8.49 grilled 7-shrimp bahn mi was on stale over-toasted bread and lacked flavor. I ended up eating just those few 60-cts and was hungry after.
2. The $3.49 cup of gumbo was mostly rice, which was actually good because it contained freakish chicken parts in an inedible anise tasting roux.
3. The $0.99 spring roll was dry and insipid.
4. The bottled cola was $1.99! And that's with no refill!

AND THEN I HAD TO DEAL WITH JERRY SPRINGER
First from the dining area's TV at a deafening decibel, and then between the owners and a threatening lady who swore she was overcharged for menthols. As one guy in line remarked, "I hope she's not packin'"!!

SO MANY BETTER, CHEAPER NEARBY ALTERNATIVES 
Los Poblanos food truck across the street, Banks Meat Market's 32" $10 swimp poboy, anything at the Big Cheezy (and they have free refills!), Ideal's taqueria, Broad & Banks Seafood's kebab or pasta or gumbo or ooey gooey or...

You wouldn't know it unless you heard about it - but the subs & sandwiches here are great.  I love the fresh bread, and usually get mine to go - since eating at a gas station is alittle off-putting.  This is a great place for service, value & quality.
Well I have been to both locations and on both locations I feel it's a "hipster" version of the food. Not bad, not good. People seem to like it but I rather pay less for better food.

Had a lovely lunch in downtown Tampa stopping at the Armature Works (Heights Public Market). Lots of cool places to eat inside the public market such as sushi, salads, sandwiches, barbecue, soul food, Cuban cuisine, wood fired pizza, ice cream, pastries, beer and cocktails and a wine bar. And a great area to walk along  the Hillsborough Riverwalk & a great children area. Must See!

Had high hopes for the Stillery after such positivity reviews on Yelp. However, the was the worst food I had in a 4 day trip in Nashville. The salads were not fresh at all, and drenched in a pretty bad dressing. Brussels sprouts were fine, but definitely could make better at home. 

Would definitely skip, much better restaurants in Nashville.
I am not a local, but visit Reno a lot.  I always stop at Big Ed's to eat.  The service is always quick and friendly. The food is way better than downtown casinos.
Great eggs Benedict. Still a hidden gem. Not crowded breakfast at all, but it should be.

A cute little house for brunch. A little bit pricey for brunch then expected but the food was good. Ingredients well thought out. It all went together. Reservations definitely recommended for inside seatings. Online reservations was easy to make. I'm all about feeling comfy and throughly enjoy sitting outside on the patio next to the propane heater. It just happen to be a beautiful sunny day out for a January. Parking very limited. You might be lucky to fine one in the back.

Located next to the Old Penitentiary, Quarry View Park, and Idaho Botanical Gardens. Parking is free on a dirt lot (they really need to pave it as it is very dusty). The lot is located across from the Old Penitentiary and I posted a satellite view picture as it can be tricky to find when driving in. Bathrooms are unisex. Two of them in the dirt parking area and not nice at all. I recommend using the Quarry View Park restrooms instead. 

The hike up to the top is doable for most people. And although it starts pretty steep the elevation rise slows down for a good portion of the middle of the hike. Round trip distance is about 3.6-3.8 miles depending on which way you go. 

Great views at the top. This is definitely a five star local hike that everyone must try. I found there to be no litter and friendly hikers along the way. There are two garbage cans at the top so pick up any litter you see and dispose of your own trash at the top if needed. 

While there is graffiti that should be removed/covered from rocks at the top of table rock they are not in view from the actual peak and seating area. 

P.S.  I removed one star for the dirt parking lot, bathrooms (they smelled bad, had lots of flies, and no toilet paper), and graffiti that could be easily covered or removed. Please fix those things city of Boise!
I can't speak for the restaurant as I've never dined there, but we get sushi delivered 3 or 4 times a month. Always fresh, great price for the city, and super speedy delivery.

This place is great.  Not only is the food great but the server made the experience. Shelley made everything that much better.  She got my fiancé and I a table right before closing and made sure everything was amazing.  She has great recommendations and really knows how to treat the guests and make you really get the New Orleans vibe. She makes you feel like you are her only table and really special.

Nothing but superlatives about this place. I went with B yesterday to get a pie for my dad (who can't do garlic) and we tried a few slices while we waited for it to be cooked (which was not a long wait at all). Service was very friendly and the place was clean.

I had the white pizza with spinach, B had a cheese slice, and we shared a slice of the greek salad pizza. Everything was fresh and tasted like it was straight out of a garden. 

My sister once got a pizza there with vegan cheese (they consider all eating types) and, while I think vegan cheese is what we'll be eating in hell for eternity, she seemed happy with it. The pie we got for my dad also had no cheese, just tomatoes and italian herbs. There was a second vegan option, too, but I couldn't bring myself to look at it (though I'm sure it was also very good).

I recommend this place, and there aren't a lot of decent places in this town.

So glad we stumbled upon this place. Its like eye candy from the moment you approach the store. Then it goes on and on, full of treasures for everyone! Staff was pleasant and helpful. This really made our weekend a success! Thanks, we will be back!

Authentic as it is gonna get. I had a few dishes from here and it is excellent. Steak with cactus, chicken Mexican style, etc. I could love here.

Service, it's just simple. Order and they bring it out. Speedy and pleasant. Parking around here is hard to find but worth the drive looking for one. Prices are pretty good here.

These are the most incompetent rude group of people who have secured contracts to tow cars and think in return that they can treat people like dirt. I showed up at 8:45 to pick up my sons car and after speaking to the idiot on the phone twice they did not let me in to pay and leave with my car until 10:15 am and unfortunately I was unable to get hold of a police officer to assist me in getting these idiots to release my car at the time they advertise office hours.
These idiots do not deserve to be in business and I hope my complaint filed at the BBB helps in getting these morons to lose their business.

Just have to say that this place is good! 
Upon walking in the front door I was greeted by a very nice young lady whom promptly seated me and my husband.
The decor reminded me of a small little villa in italy. The music volume was nice.(not to loud)
We decided on the family style meal, Shrimp fettucinne and chicken marsala which also come with a small personal size pizza. However our server mentioned that we could upgrade the size of the pizza. YAY!! Leftovers.
Got to say food was great, plentiful and priced right.
We will be back.

The staff was super friendly. And this is probably the cleanest westshore location I have been in. I was there up until closing. Not once did I feel rushed or pressured to hurry and leave. Everyone was awesome to interact with. They've got a great crew at this location. Totally going out of my way to go to this one from now 

The only downside is the parking lot is on the smaller side and it can be a bit tricky getting in and out of the plaza.

Visited for the first time on a Saturday. Thankfully made reservations because the place was jam packed with hour or more waits. 

Nice place although if loud isn't your thing, this may not be your style. 

Food was excellent as was our waiter and the bus staff. 

Ordered the bruschetta and fried calamari to start. Bruschetta was fresh herbs and tomato's on a nice crispy toast. Calamari was not fancy seasoning-wise but it was cooked nicely and was tender. 

Second course was insalata di arance alla siciliana. Fresh mixed greens and oranges with a nice citrus olive oil dressing. 

Wife had the black truffle sacchetti and loved it while I did a traditional rigatoni carbonara with a side of meatballs. I hadn't had carbonara in a while and this didn't disappoint creamy and salty with past done perfectly. Three big meatballs with flavorful red sauce on the side made the dinner. 

Slightly pricey for two but I'd recommend if you're looking for a new Italian place to try. Maybe hit it up on a weeknight to see if it's quieter. 

Definitely going back.

Mean service, but there Chinese I get it....

that's not the bad portion... the beef and broccoli was weird. The beef was covered in fuzzys and hairs and tasted like fish...

Cooked to order my ass

After being a member at LA Fitness Signature for almost a year and a half I decided to cancel my membership. Initially, this gym was great, but this gym has multiple issues.

OVERCROWDED
As more members have joined this gym and the gym is reaching full capacity LA Fitness has become too crowded. Between peak hours 5 to 7pm Mondays thru Fridays it is nearly impossible to get a parking spot. Once you find parking there is usually a wait for cardio and weight equipment.

CLASS SCHEDULE
The class schedule doesn't change often so the class times either work for you or they don't. In my case, they did not. I wanted to take cycle classes, but they were always at 5:30pm or 7pm. I would have also liked to seen more of  a variety of classes offered.

CLEANLINESS 
There is always a film of dust and dirt on the cup holders and television screens of the ellipticals and treadmills as well as the fans on the treadmills. It doesn't help that the South Tampa members feel too entitled to wipe down the machines after using them. 

TOWELS (or lack of)
If you work out during peak hours it is not uncommon for the gym to run out of towels. For $50/month you would think LA Fitness could afford to buy more towels. If the members aren't returning the towels my suggestion is to have members trade their keys or ID for a towel. When members return their towel they get their keys or ID back. 

DESIGN
While the floor to ceiling glass windows look attractive from the outside these windows cause several issues in the club. The cardio floor is miserable during the day because the sun is shining on the treadmills and ellipticals. The glare of the sunlight also makes it difficult to see the television sets on the cardio equipment. The windows also provide no privacy so everyone on Dale Mabry can watch you work out and those walking by the pool/hot tub area can see everything.

While I still believe LA Fitness is one of the better gym options in Tampa this "Signature Club" did not meet my expectations.
Huuuuge takes foreeeeeever to get through security most of the time and my flights are always laaaaate and I can't afford any of the fooood

Imagine having a bride cry on the phone a week before the wedding because the venue is overbooked, everyone said yes and now menus have to change- this was Mike's experience and Mike said 'you are the bride, we will do whatever we can!' And he did! People are still talking about the Mac & Cheese and my aunt and uncle have been trying to recreate our catfish with spicy mustard ap for weeks! The perogi reminded me of my Grandmother's! My husband and I come from three cultures and we wanted a caterer with the ability to capture those meals to share with our new families. Mike not only did it, but he went above and beyond and even changed from stations to family style as more family flew out for our wedding. It was the perfect choice and he did an amazing job! He isn't just involved in food, he was at every meeting, every phone call- he even picked up something he didn't have to that I forgot! I feel like Mike loves what he does, not just catering, but weddings too and I KNOW my friends will go to him! Also, we were on a budget (isn't everyone?) and I went to 10 caterers- not only was he one of the few with a tasting (and we tasted and approved everything) but his per person cost for a Philadelphia wedding can not be touched! Love Mike and loved our day! (Wedding was 6/27/15)

We've been brining our dogs here for 4 years.  The number of mistakes and errors has been increasing over the last few visits -- from billing to being prepared for appointments.  A certain number of mistakes are to be expected with any process, but one rub is that they expect us to compensate for their errors.  Our last visit's unpreparedness cost us 1.5 hours of waiting for a routine medication that was schedule weeks in advance and an mistake in the billing (albeit less than 5% of the total bill) was annoying and added further evidance of a lackluster system. The staff clearly cares for animals but leadership and direction from owner(s) appears to be missing as the the attention to detail is substandard.  My fear is that this also occurs back-of-house where we have no way of knowing.  I don't chance my dog's health when I have a lack of confidence in a provider and will be moving on.

Food is OK.  The people are great and it's in a wonderful part of town.  Would much rather have had drinks and apps.  The meals are a bit bland and not really worth the moderate pricing.  In California you gotta be spot on with your Mexican food or just go Italian.

This is Modern's Satellite restaurant--YAY!  I love it. It has been one of my favorite quick stops for tapas since it's opened. Situated below a modern apartment complex, it's bright, with a wall of windows, spacious, spotless clean & has lot's of unique decor. They offer beautiful, hearty soups, a smallish, inventive, tapas menu (I hope they add a few more), some other plates and a divine cheese plate and charcuterie spread too. You can choose to combine the two for a little more $, and both would easily feed 2 people as a meal or 4 people as an appetizer.  I don't feel that the price point is unfair, but it adds up quickly especially when drinking and getting tapas so take heed. In additional to all of this awesomeness,  the sommelier is wonderful. He's quick on his feet to help you pick out a great wine, he's engaging and he knows his stuff! Extra Bonus!  I haven't seen much turnover since they opened, which is a great sign in regards to pay, work environment and management. The staff are usually smiling, very helpful and quick to help!  The chefs are equally knowledgeable and friendly. The patio space outside is expansive, and can seat quite a few people and it's ultra modern furniture is surprisingly comfortable!  I will be back often!
Over-priced and over-rated; even charge for admission to playground!  Ridiculous!
The place is kind of strange but the owner makes delicious food! The space is super interesting and definitely a great experience.

My family and I drove down from Arroyo Grande to see my nephew and his gal, and to have some Vietnamese grub.  This is a good little mom and pop type noodle house.  The flavors and presentation are simple yet adequate.  I did not expect hardcore vietnamese food that you get in the bigger population centers...  everything was tasty and prepared well... go and enjoy!  This is a basic, all purpose Vietnamese cafe and does the triick nicely.

The people were friendly and the service was fast. I never been here before; however I was flying back to Dallas so I ordered a suitcase of burgers. I didn't know, that burgers became luggage... Bless the man or woman who came up with this idea... The burgers were a magical experience... I ate them like popcorn... Just kept popping them in while driving to the airport; however not a good idea when flying back when the plane has turbulence and only 2 bathrooms. Let's just say, God and I had a great conversation on the flight home.

I'll keep going back.
I had a glazed donut. It was yummy. My boyfriend had a sausage, egg, and cheese biscuit. He said it tasted homemade. He loved it! Very friendly staff. You should go there.

We've been twice now for takeout. The noodles are fresh. The taste is pretty authentic. It was recommended to me by a coworker. And it was worth it. I always love the noodles and the portions are great. They don't skimp on meat. They give you lots of soup if you get the soup. And always lots of noodles. Highly recommend for anyone looking for authentic Chinese noodle dishes.

Dr T. Is the man too see! great environment this guy did miracles on my knee now I'm playing ball again like I used to thanks to him! I recommend this place to anyone that has issues with their body go see DR T!!!!!

I've been here a few times already, and I really love this place.  It's a great neighborhood pub and has such a homey atmosphere.  The draft beer selection is always rotating and there seem's to be something for everyone.  We've sat at the bar, in the bar area and in the dining room and have had great service in all spots.  Everything we've ordered for food (burgers, pasta, fish, salads) so far has tasted great, My only complaint is that it gets a little crowded on Friday and Saturday nights!

This place makes me fat !!  sometimes I hate that the food is so delicious . I think I have had to go up two sizes since this place opened . I LOVE the pizza the sauce is fabulous . Service is always tops . I highly recommend this establishment . I'm so glad big booties are in .

Went here with friends In time for their Happiness hour.  Many things to choose from. We decided on the Vegas roll, lettuce with chicken wraps, cucumber and crab salad, potstickers, and crab Rangoon.  Our server was very friendly. Our food came out quickly. We all enjoyed everything at a very reasonable price.  The decor is nice as well.
Excellent customer service with a great selection of bikes & accessories. Very helpful & friendly staff.
The food is wonderful and atmosphere is great. My favorite fish is the lasooni gobhi, onion bhajia and baingan bhartha. Definitely would love to come back here again.

I first visited First Watch a couple years ago and was disappointed. Over the past two years, I've eaten here a dozen times and progressively enjoyed it more and more.

I had brunch with my sister here this morning, and we both agreed that First Watch is a smart restaurant that attracts a diverse crowd--after all, who doesn't love a good breakfast?! 

My staple here is the Burrito Vera Cruz with extra potatoes substituted for the fruit (ha, that's a no-brainer). The servers are always polite and very agreeable to making changes to menu items. When I go for lunch, I usually opt for the Heard of Buffalo Chicken Wrap with bleu cheese. Very tasty!

I'm not a coffee drinker, but my friends seem to be in unanimous agreement that the coffee at First Watch is terrible--hence the four stars instead of five.

Side note: some of the servers here are attractive--perhaps First Watch is the training grounds for servers who aspire to work at the ultimate beautiful servers' restaurant--J. Alexanders, of course.
Amazing office, professional, staff is happy, website is user friendly and the medical expertise is A++! Keep up the great hard work you all do in helping others.

One word... Chocolate peanut butter ice cream... K maybe more than one word. Simply delicious to the point where I'm craving it and make the drive from downtown to whyte ave and have even made a point to go in mid rainstorm. I've only tried the entrees once before and they were pretty delicious from what I recall. I had a late night chai latte on a date with my boyfriend a few weeks before and it tasted very authentic and didn't taste like the typical chai syrup that is generally used, I could be wrong, but it tasted great. I had a taste of my bfs latte as well and I was impressed. It is pretty hard to find a good latte around town. We were both impressed by the amount of cakes/pies available and might have to add on to my chocolate peanut delight on my next visit. 
One negative thing I must mention...one of the last times I went, I went with my mom who is particular about a lot of things and does have strong opinions, but for once I did have to agree that this was unacceptable..We went in to grab some ice cream..the line was long but not out of control, so when it was our turn to order I had my scoop quickly filled and then the girl behind the case accidentally dropped the scoop on the floor..what does one usually do when something like that happens especially in a food establishment..? Get a new utensil to use or properly sanitizing the dropped tool. well, this young blonde decided that a quick splash of water was appropriate and continued to scoop on. Naturally my mother reacted and yet the girl still didn't even attempt to do anything about it and instead tried to defend her spray off as an appropriate reaction. Needless to say, not OK. If I witness something like that again I wont be returning even for my beloved ice cream. Maybe an appropriate orientation to the obviously naive young girl about food safety would be recommended.
This was a great place chicken piccata was great. Asian stir fry very good. Drinks top shelf. Bartender was a great woman. Stay off broadway it's a waste. Come here.

Absolute best donut place in Idaho. I came from California where my favorite donut shop was Spudnuts. Sadly we don't have that here in Idaho. I tried many different donut places and when I landed on DK Donuts on a whim, I was in heaven! Delicious donuts, great prices, friendly family-run business. They even made me a batch of fresh apple fritters when I came in to buy a donut in the middle of the afternoon - JUST BECAUSE. How awesome is that? I ended up buying a dozen of them when I only went in for one!

I have no idea why this place has so many stars. The soft tortillas were cold and clearly right from the package.  My husband got beef and chicken tacos and I got enchiladas verses. Both were tasteless.

Food is okay. But there were gnats that kept landing in our food. When we notified the waitstaff, she just said, "Yes, we have a bug problem right now. All I can do is give you another plate to cover your food."
The staff is very welcoming and the restaurant was nice and airy. We had a large group and felt they did an excellent job accommodating us. The food and drinks were great!
Great food, great service not so great margaritas. Would def go back though. Loved the atmosphere and authenticity of the place.

It regarded so inviting we determined to have lunch outdoor. We can't wait to go lower back!! One of those few restaurant stories where you may virtually do not forget what you had because it changed into so amazingly appropriate. Looking forward to our subsequent go to!

I am so disappointed with this pharmacy, they advertised on face book that they would have gloves, sanitizer, masks and a few other things available on Wednesday.
I went early around 9:30, I asked if any sanitizer was available, first tech cashier said No, tomorrow, I said I texted someone and they said it would be available today, the other tech passed her a small bottle, first tech said ok and said this is compounded in pharmacy, as she rang me up, I walked around and asked how much powder free gloves were, she said 14.00, I passed on them. I gave her cash and she gave my change I shoved the money away. When I got in the car I looked at the receipt, 4 oz of alcohol was 11.50 plus tax, I looked at the ingredients but all was in there was alcohol, no aloe or moisturizer, and the label said non sterile. I'm thinking if it's non sterile it was not  mixed under a sterile hood, so what's the big deal about making it in house?
I do have the ad from fb and the prices on other sanitizers were advertised at 5.80 per ml, that's 5.80 an ounce? I know alcohol isn't that expensive. Wow, you could have sold these at a fair price for people in need, and the neighbors would have been grateful, instead it seems that your greed got the better of this establishment.

Decided to try this place for lunch. The restaurant itself has a nice setting and open floor plan. I also loved the concept of the bread bar which they offer for free.  However the creamy crab soup lacked crab and was very watery. They were also out of one soup on the menu. The 2 wraps we ordered were just ok, nothing special. Will I ever be back? No....

I'm glad it's taking them so long to bring the check cause now I am stuck here and inspired to write a review- which I never do! I honestly don't know where to begin. Food is awful. Service is...not a thing here! Waiter was rude and maybe high? Didn't know what penne a la vodka was. But at least there is consistency as apparently the kitchen doesn't know what penne a la vodka is either. Anyway the place really sucks. If it's between this and death it's a toss up...idk at least death isn't a waste of money.
Had a great pizza.  Perfect size for two.  Good wine, good service, and fair price.  We would def. Go back.  :)
Best Italian restaurant in Philly. Their recipes are unique and the chef does a great job. Service has been excellent every time we've been there.

H&C is a great local place to get a cup of good coffee.  They have an excellent selection of beans that you can have served any way, including pour-over.  They also have a fantastic tea selection that has been recently refined.  I would say it's on par with Teavana.  

The service is ALWAYS friendly and fast.  I usually order the same thing time and time again: large americano, black.  It is fantastic every time.  If I'm feeling indulgent, their cappuccino is a winner, too.  Good selection of backed-goods, I'm partial to the 'better morning muffin' or a nice dipped biscotti.

Usually there are plenty of places to sit, but can sometimes get crowded later on Saturday or Sunday mornings.  Good WiFi and power outlets are at most tables for your devices.

This will be my go-to for morning brew and treats, or if I need a place to escape with my tablet or laptop.

This is a delightful little park. There is a playground for kids which is really very good. It doesn't separate the little ones from the bigger ones, but few parks do. There's a series of walking and bike paths to take through the grounds. None of them are especially great, but they are a very pleasant way to spend a weekend afternoon. I'm not a birder, but friends of mine who are tell me there is some very good bird watching there. It is clean, well ordered, and the bathrooms are about as clean as public restrooms in parks ever get. It is worth your time.

Ok. My first time here yesterday (6-23-18), for my friend's birthday. It was CROWDED! The wait was maybe about 30 minutes We needed a table for 9 people. While we waited for our people to come, some of us went to the bar for a Bow Wow, the cost is $12.13. It's filled with rum and vodka. DRINK SLOWLY. It will have you LIT.COM, it's really good! Finally when a majority of our people came (7, we just decided to go in without our other 2 people, or they was going to pull our table) but the hostess who showed us to our table had a nasty attitude because all of our people wasnt there and we told her we will not wait on them, just seat us. THEN, the other hostess gave us the wrong info on the checks. She told us we can only have ONE check,but THANKS TO OUR WONDERFUL AND AMAZING SERVER, VICTORIA..she gave us the correct information. We could do up to 4 cards and the rest cash. Victoria was the best. THANK YOU GIRL, IF YOU CAN READ THIS, YOU WERE GREAT TO US! I'm giving 4 stars because of the hostess. Also, and the food was great! It took a while for it to come out, but we were having too much fun to notice. Appetizers were great and the entrees!!! It was also freshly hot!!! We will have to secretly come back, but not for a special occasion, just for spur of the moment.

For the best boneless chicken wings at an amazing price...you must try Whiskey River!  There are a wide variety of flavors from very gentle to fire breathing.  Sit out on the deck over looking the Cotee River while you're served by a very friendly staff.

First the place is empty and the two ladies who were working there were really rude, didn't even try to offer small talk, and was very curt with me. But mainly she saw my designer bag and saw dollar signs because she tried to over price me. When I walked in there is no signs or menus on what they have available for services and prices. Secondly, when I asked how much a regular mani cost she said $17 but I wanted French tip- nothing fancy not powder just good old fashioned polish, and she paused and was like $25. Okay.. steep but sure. Until when I was drying my nails I noticed a book where they kept how much they charge and it said $17 for a basic manicure and $5 extra for French... that's $22 not $25. When I confronted her about this she became even more rude and said bs about supply and demand and how everyone charges at least $10 extra for French! Lol what?! In what universe?! Ladies be careful with this place...

Great service from our waitress.  Busy Saturday night, but we went to the restaurant website and you can't make reservations,  but you can get "in line ".  We arrived at 600pm and after telling the hostess we had arrived we were seated in less than 10 minutes, similar parties told me they were waiting past 30 minutes so I  recommend that you  go online to get on the wait list. I ordered  a Fontini Chicken pasta which was a seasonal favorite, however about 10 minutes after we ordered I was told they were out and I had to order something else.  I ended up ordering a Parmesan crusted chicken which was OK.  The restaurant was kind enough not to ask me to pay for the Parmesan chicken and Comped me the meal.  To run out of a meal at 600pm prime dinner time on a Saturday evening costed A Star. However I do appreciate the complimentary meal.
