BOI is a medium sized airport. The rental car lot is within walking distance to the exit of the baggage claim. Seems like everything flows pretty well, ticketing, TSA, food court and terminals. The airport is very well taken care off and the employees all have been friendly the two times I've been here. There are also several restaurants in terminal B with bars that pretty nice to hangout while waiting for your flight. I would definitely use this airport again.
Second best Margerittas  in town. When we showed up they were playing fun local live music.

Came back here on a Sunday evening to try some more stuff.  The experience was mixed.

Once again, kicked off with the Calamari in Ginger Juice for an app ($6).  Once again, it was fantastic. 

I took the advice of Zach X. and tried the Shredded Pork w/ Garlic Sauce ($9).  It was pretty damn good, with flavors that reminded me of hot and sour soup.  It was a bit too saturated in sauce, however.  Great portion and plenty to take home.

Now the not-so-good.  We wanted a vegetable dish so we went for the "Chinese Vegetable Surprise" or something like that ($8).  It was a gamble that did not pay off.  It was basically a ton of bok choy leaves with pieces of tomato and eggplant, drowned in some sort of brown sauce.  Unfortunately the sauce was kind of slimy.  I couldn't imagine actually eating a piece of the slimy bok choy.  I did pick off some of the pieces of eggplant which were also slimy, but pretty tasty.  But overall I really can't see anyone enjoying this dish.

Our service, while friendly, was not very attentive.  We had to flag the waitress down a couple times.  They seemed understaffed.

I won't dock any stars because I still think Joy Luck is a gem.  But I will be a bit more cautious next time.

When you go to Philadelphia you get a cheesesteak. On a recent trip, I opted to skip the popular Pat's, Gino's and Tony Luke's cheesesteak institutions and try Jimmy G's Steaks.

One of the newest cheesesteak spots to hit the Philly scene, Jimmy G's is only a few years old. It's located in the Spring Garden area of Philly and has a sleek shiny steel interior and outdoor seating area. This place has also fully embraced social media, with TV screens and billboards showcasing recent Yelp reviews and photos.

After devouring a cheesesteak with Cheez Whiz and onions and some fries, I have to say Jimmy G's can compete with the best of them. The bread was extremely fresh, the meat well-seasoned and nothing beats Cheez Whiz. Check them out next time you're looking for something that's a little less crowded than the usual spots.
great place to eat good prices good drinks good atmosphere good food best Mexican restaurant in St Louis

In the words of Charles Barkley, the not-so quality inn was turrible. My flight was cancelled, so I booked this dump and it took an hour to get a shuttle to their motel. The front desk "lady" told me that I didn't have a reservation, which I did and after 6 phone calls, they finally answered. I know it's not the Ritz Carlton, but if I pay $119 for a room in a crappy part of town (not sure there is a good part of town in St. Louis), I feel like it should be moderate. The whole place smelled like a Dave Matthews concert, which would have been fine if I wanted a little contact high, but I did not. I just wanted to sleep on my pee-stained bed. As I stared at the ceiling, I thought that it would collapse on me from the two people going at it above me. It got weird. Last but not least, I got a wake-up call at 3:00 am. The only problem is I did not ask for a wake-up call at 3:00 am. Room 249 is not the same as 246. Hey, I get it, a 6 is an upside down 9 and there was probably a toddler running the front desk.  I am disgruntled and I will remain disgruntled until I get a refund.

My cousin and several family members stayed here over the weekend. I did not book a room here but spent tons of time in many different rooms and all over the property.

If it weren't for the nasty ass out dated smelly rooms this place would be a 5. But since most people go to resorts and have to spend time in their rooms, you would think a resort that has security at the gate would be a whole lot nicer. 

One room smelled of smoke sooooo bad. 

The pool was SPECTACULAR though kids were just running everywhere, forget about enjoying the hot tub, as there were little kids in there as well even though there are signs that state it is not allowed. 

The little market is extremely over priced, for 9 bottles of water, 4 bags of chips and several candy bars the bill was $50 dollars! No lie! 

The property is nice, the staff is nice. I just wouldn't book here thinking you are getting a high end resort as that is soooo far from the case.

Simply put totally gross.  Both my husband and I got the Caroline pulled Pork platter.  What we got was a plate full of fat covered in BBQ sauce.  When we walked in there was no smell of smoked meat it kind of smelled like disinfectant. Baked beans were definitely not fresh made they tasted like canned beans. Potato salad had absolutely NO flavor. We will definitely NOT be going back for seconds! The five star ratings must be from employes, family members or the owners honestly it deserves less than one star.

This hotel is ideal for someone who is looking for a place to stay for a night. I wouldn't suggest this hotel for anything longer than a night (or two, max). It's a small room but if you need a place to crash for the night, it serves it's purpose. My girlfriend and I were recently there and it was a very stressful situation. 

After speaking to a nice woman named Danielle, I made our reservation over the phone. I happened to call back the following day with a quick question. The man with a very strong Indian accent (I can't use the word "gentleman" because he was one of the MOST rude, ignorant individuals I have ever come across) I spoke to on the phone, (his name was Paul) could not find our reservation even after supplying him with the confirmation number 3 times and spelling out my last name several times as well. Paul did not seem to care if he found our reservation in the system or not. Finally after going back and forth with someone who clearly did not want to offer any type of assistance, I asked to speak to someone else (preferably someone I could understand clearly). 

The next person that I reached was yet another man with a very strong Indian accent. His name was Harry and he identified himself as the manager. Finally, he found my reservation in their system but told me that I made the reservation two weeks past the date in which I had reserved the room. I clearly know when I made the reservation for yet this man insisted that I was wrong. Come to find out, Danielle must have incorrectly marked us down in the incorrect date/slot which was a honest mistake. After another 15-20 minutes of being on the phone, Harry squeezed me into another slot on the day in which I had originally  booked the room for. Ahhh finally, it's all taken care of. NOPE! 

Upon opening the email confirmation within minutes of getting off the phone, I find out that the cost of the room which I had booked was now almost DOUBLE the price! I immediately called back and Paul told me that Harry was not available as he was in a meeting. After explaining the situation to Paul (who still did not seem to care to help me whatsoever), I became increasingly frustrated. Paul told me that no one except Harry can change the price back to what I was originally quoted and now instead of being in a meeting, I was told that Harry was gone for the weekend and would not return until after our visit. Clearly, he had lied to me and for some reason; did not want me to speak to Harry. Paul continued to yell at me, speak to me like a piece of trash and told me that he will not do anything to help me resolve this situation. I explained to him that TWO people there at the hotel quoted me a specific price, yet the confirmation I was sent showed a price nearly double. 

Being that this hotel is a subsidiary of a large corporation such as Wyndham, I explained to Paul that I will then call the corporate phone number and explain this situation to them and inform them how unprofessional he has been. His response was "go ahead and call, I don't care what you do". Way to keep it classy Microtel front desk guy! 

Now, after another 45 minutes of being on the phone with the customer care representative and explaining the situation once again; I was told that there was nothing they could do to resolve the situation until they investigate it further and get back to me within 4-5 days. Lovely! After being defeated and clearly frustrated, I hung up.

We arrived at the Microtel around 3:00pm the following day and who do I find at the front desk? Yep, Paul. Employee of the Year looking miserable and speaking extremely rude to us and other customers. His face clearly matched the rude voice on the phone. As he proceeded to check us in, I explained who I was and he said "yeah I remember you and there is nothing I can do". I noticed another female employee there and upon reading her name tag, I noticed that it was Danielle who I originally spoke to. 

When I asked to speak to her, Paul said "yeah go over and talk to her" instead of offering to get Danielle's attention for a customer seeking assistance. So by now, I had to walk outside to track down Danielle who I have never met before. Little did I know, her work shift was over and she was getting ready to leave. I apologized for bothering her and explained who I was and the horrible situation that I have been through. Thankfully she recognized who I was and remembered speaking to me. 

She came back inside the hotel and informed Paul the correct price amount which I was quoted by herself and the manager. She must have needed proper authorization to manually change a price in their computer and made the necessary calls. The whole time, Paul stood there and did not offer to help at all. While Danielle finished checking us in, she apologized for the hassle. 

Had it not been for her, we would have spent nearly twice as much to stay there. Big thanks for her for taking the time to help us when Paul treated us like trash!
Best burger in the area by far. Everything is made with high quality ingredients. Good decor and excellent service. Finally a truly interesting menu on the Mainline.

Since being in Tampa for 3 months I decided its time to find a better place to get a haircut than Sportsclips.  Im used to paying $40+ for haircuts and this was no exception.  However, I used to have more hair and needed more technical snipping done.  I probably couldve waited another week or so to justify paying $40 because I really didn't get much taken off at all.  So that being said, I wasn't explained options on pricing for my haircut.  But I was given the "experience" tour of the place and Dillion's customer service was excellent.  The products are excellent.  The staff is excellent.  The 13" tube tv's are not so excellent for a high-end salon.

Best naan in Pinellas county. Again today, can't believe how much I love the lunch buffet. 7+ entrees, 4 chutney choices, 2 rice options, 2 desserts. All regularly refilled. Courteous staff. I'm a huge fan.

Thoroughly enjoy this restaurant. Definitely top 2 on Mass Ave. If you do not like communal seating, you may want to stear clear of this restaurant. Even though you can get 2-4 top tables, it m may be a long wait for those. I enjoy communal seating so I'm fine here. 

I'm a duck person so their duck and waffle was delicious. Wish there was more of the duck but that's a good thing because I've come back for more. 

Great atmosphere and they serve tasteful spirits.

Finally gotsta try the infamous spicy chicken sandwich! Virgin no more! Bun was soft, crunchy coating and a whole piece of chicken breast.

Easy and clean place. I really love their Popeyes sweet and un-sweetened brewed tea.

Want to try the sides and whole chicken pieces next time.
The best, simply and easily. You pay a premium but you don't deal with all the issues. The Genius Bar is by far the best solve it people around. Most of the time the issue is me and solved for free.

It was ok.  The inside is dark, but its a Belgian style bar.  The beer selection was great and they had ciders!  The hamburger was adequate, nothing to write home about like I had been told.  The french fries were seasoned well, but the hype definitely was undeserved.  I will try sitting outside next time, but there is quite some construction going on in the neighborhood.

The chef has some ingredient proportion issues:

In a PESTO PIZZA, there was too much goat cheese and too many sun dried tomatoes, and too little pesto sauce. Do not get this.

GREEK SALAD, not your typical greek salad. hardly any lettuce. too much vinegar, and too many peppers. oh, and that giant bowl of salad costs $10, totally not worth it. 

GUACAMOLE and CHIPS. Yummy, but I would recommend toning down on the spiciness in the guac, and offers a bit more chips.

Come during happy hour for drinks and pizza specials.

Will I come back? No, I would check out other pizza places the next time I'm in Reno.

This place has been on my must-try list and I am glad I finally gave it a visit. I love deli's but must most of them have inconvenient hours and close pretty early but 51st Deli is open till 8pm on the weekdays. We got a parking spot right up front and ordered our sandwiches without any wait.

We came for dinner but they serve breakfast all day and I took full advantage by ordering the Beta Feta. It is a pretty simple sandwich (egg, tomato, avocado & feta on an everything bagel) but somehow they made it taste extra good. Despite it being so late in the day, the bagel tasted super fresh and the eggs were fresh off the griddle. Absolutely worth the $6. My friend ordered the Nations sandwich and was underwhelmed. It looked like it was half the size of my sandwich and it cost $2 more. Around the deli counter were a bunch of individually packaged desserts (pies, cheesecakes, cannolis). I definitely need to come back and try those!

There is a fair amount of indoor seating with some smaller and longer picnic style tables. Everything seemed very clean. They even had disinfectant spray at each table with the condiments.

It's a cheap hotel. So of course you get what you pay for. We stayed in the 5th floor, room 507. The room was small, very small. The walls were super thin so you can hear police sirens, drunk people outside and the neighbors. We had to crank up the AC so we didn't have to hear all the extra annoying noises. The restroom was the worst part of the room. It was dirty, the water pressure is seriously a joke. The bed was very noisy, every time we moved (if you catch my drift) the bed squeaked and squeaked and squeaked. Annoying. The only good thing was the location, it was walking distance to the beach and restaurants.

Good food and you truly feel welcome and taken care of. This place is no joke. Just moved to the area and stopped in one weekday for lunch with the wife. Owner spent 10 mins talking to us before ordering and suggested some of the favorites. Food was awesome, shakes were great. Being from Buffalo they couldn't top my favorite from home but def a run for their money! Keeps up the good work! Also cool that they somehow bring in famous people all the time. Very cool!

The apple fritter was very good, wish I would have gotten picture. Barely made it to the car before I was taking a bite. I will be back very soon. Other donuts were average, good thing came for apple fritter. The people were friendly very warm atmosphere.

My experience begins with a phone call. Tried to use their poorly designed app, got frustrated, called in. Side note( please take note from Dominos user friendly app) girl who took the call seemed frustrated, unenthused, and frankly bothered she had to work. I ordered the special. One large pizza with 2 toppings for 8.99. I ordered half tomatoes and half extra cheese. Very simple. I then ordered a double order of their boneless wings (horrible). My total was $35. We will get to that later...,

My order came relatively quickly and the delivery guy was friendly. I sit down to eat and notice the tomatoes are all over the entire pizzza. I call in and speak with Anthony(the manager present) Anthony wanted argue with me that I didn't know what I had ordered and that he would send me another at 50% off. He was combative, argumentative, and ignorant of the situation. Instead of sending another pizza less than a mile away he will lose the opportunity to ever gain my business and anyone I know. But what does he care. He's an hourly employee, with poor understanding of business acumen, and but I feel badly for the owner.....

The wings were $18 for 20 small pieces with no ranch, which I ordered as well. Never got to that point with Anthony.....
A family friendly divebar that carves a mean roast beef.

Awesome little neighborhood bar just across the street from Ochsner hospital. I've passed by this place many times but have only ducked in just recently. They have a pretty awesome selection of beers on tap, both local and imports as well as a great selection of bottles in the "medicine cabinet". Darts, pool and video poker are also in house. Great for groups for after work get togethers or to duck in for a beer after a long day in the hospital.

Karaoke on Fridays, darts tournaments on odd Saturdays and live music on even saturdays. They also do crawfish boils and shot specials (i.e. free shots when the ambulance passes by, free shots when the Saints get a touchdown). 25 cent wings on Fridays and a menu full pretty standard (but cheap and delicious) pub grub.

I had to dock a star because they still allow smoking inside; if they could just make it a nonsmoking bar (like the hospital they draw a lot of business from) they'd be a solid five star bar.

Spent the night at the Marriott next to longwood gardens and popped in here for a quite bite before heading home! 

My girlfriend loved the summer coffee! She had the spicy eggs and I got the eggs and prosciutto on salad! 

The eggs were really fresh! And the provolone cheese melted on my eggs and prosciutto was the perfect amount of sharp when combined with the salad dressing. It came with a red pepper type of sauce that I did not like (I ordered ToGo so this was in its own small container on the side so I was glad). The dressing was like a Dijon vinaigrette that complimented the arugula and eggs really well.   

The ambiance was so modern and fresh and the staff were very polite and patient. They answered all of our questions and gave great suggestions! 

The bathrooms are unisex which is always a plus.
It's not Tony Lukes But It's pretty good according to my friend Who had one last night Mine was a little messy But it was good once I worked it right and used a fork

Once again work finds me in a far flung place looking for food! The receptionist at the hotel recommended this place even though she doesn't particularly care for Mexican food she says this is really good stuff. So I am here to find out, I find the place a short walk away and it appears to be in a warehouse type metal building. A nice awning out front provides sufficient shade to keep the interior reasonably cool. Upon entering I am taken aback by the number of staff who are not "Mexican" although fortunately I get a Hispanic server with a great knowledge of the menu.  The house salsa and complimentary chips are brought out and a drink order taken, they have no Horchata however they have great sweet tea. I am presented the menu and I ordered some of the homemade guacamole.  It has a decent flavor however it appears to have a lot of pico in it and it could stand a squeeze of lime.  There is good crowd here and a festive mood seems to have settled over the place. I quickly dispose of the chips salsa and guacamole yeah I know what was I thinking. So now that I'm not nearly as hungry as I thought I was I ordered a couple Shrimp quesadillas and request my onions grilled well.  There is plenty of shrimp and the flavor appears to be just about there however there are no limes with the plate and the onions are undercooked. I give it 4 stars for the following,  I asked twice for limes and my onions were very undercooked. However all other aspects are excellent! Y'all give them a try and rate them for yourselves. As for me I will be back!

Michele did alterations on my wedding dress and working with her was incredible.  She was so calming and knowledgeable that my stress levels immediately dropped and I was 100% confident she would make my dress perfect. And perfect it was! Her skill is top notch and absolutely affordable. Going directly to a seamstress can save monday rather than having it done by bridal gown store since they add on a percentage to the seamstress's fee in addition. Go with Michele and you won't regret it!

Fantastic sandwiches. Got the QT special for $6.50, and it's incredibly filling and cheap! Bread was crispy and airy. Meat was fresh and loved the sauce and touch of cilantro in it. Definitely a great spot to get food that's cheap And convenient

The guys in the shop are great. Personable, attentive, and know what they're talking about. The installers, however, were a totally different story. Nice guys, but messed up several times. They forgot to install a pressure hose within my washer which subsequently flooded my basement. They also didn't put the hinges back on my door before leaving. I left three or four messages on their machine for the service department  (after nobody picked up) which all went unanswered. When a repair tech finally came out the next week, he was very pleasant and fixed the installer's mistake within five minutes. I never heard from Dominic's afterwards. It's a shame, because I really want to use a neighborhood store and build that relationship after buying my new house about two blocks from the shop, but this is not the level of service I'd ever expect.

FAB, I mean fab, coffee.  Maybe the best anywhere.  They also do a great job with breakfast when I normally go.  It is just about always crowded in that "brunch" weekend  time.  You might freak seeing the line and be tempted to bolt.  But, somehow, it works itself out that by the time you place your order at the register, there will be a spot for you and your companion.  The owner does a good job with keeping things cheerful in the line by taking coffee orders ahead of time.  Def worth a visit for the weekend breakfast fix.

Look no further for an outstanding calzone because my boyfriend and I stopped in here and were absolutely blown away!! The garlic butter sauce is better than any ordinary one you get from dominos or Pizza Hut and it has a beautiful/unique atmosphere. As if we weren't impressed enough by the food, we figured out that they have the same lemonade and soft drinks as Sugar Fire . The service was quick and accurate for those in a rush for lunch!

Steak n Shake food is always good no matter where you go but that doesn't mean the service is the same. If you want somewhat fast service this is NOT the place to go. My boyfriend and I went to Steak 'n Shake and it took 10-15 mins to get our drinks. I think what the situation was that Washington street Steak 'n Shake does not have good teamwork. They don't let their teammates know they have a table waiting for them and the poor sever ends up with shitty attitude people. GET WITH IT STEAK N SHAKE AND GET A BETTER TEAM!

I'm constantly at this wawa, this morning I got my usual coffee and breakfast sandwich and bought a pack of pods for my vape. I asked the cashier to my stuff in a bag. I leave to go to work, get to work and realize she didn't put my vape pods in my bag, mind you they cost 13 dollars. She also didn't give me a receipt or offer one to me. I just lost 13 dollars with no chance to get a refund or my product back because she didn't give me a receipt to prove my purchase. I lost my money and they lost a customer.

Just had a baby shower on the balcony of State & Fig and it was just perfect! Marisa the owner couldn't have been sweeter or easier to work with, the staff was professional and very helpful, the food was excellent and fairly priced, and the location was lovely.  I've eaten here once before and felt the same way as I did this time, love this place! I've had the Fig 'n Toast and the BLT and others at my table raved about the burger-all were impressed and happy with their food. 

Excellent restaurant that I will definitely be recommending to my friends!

I really hate leaving bad reviews. Everyone has had bad service occasionally, or once in a while the place is having an off night. This was atrocious and I rarely ever use that word in a public setting. I could see from our table that we weren't the only ones in distress. Read on...

We were seated immediately, and as the server changed television channels to find the futbol game, we were ignored for almost 10 minutes. Both servers walked past our table with little care that we had even been seated, and I can understand if you are slammed and you are behind, but at this point in the evening, we were one of three tables in the entire place. The focus was on the soccer game. Around the 10 minute mark we contemplated leaving, but just as I decided to leave the server asks us for drink orders and if we were ready to order. Sure..., if we had menus.

Once we received our menus, we quickly caught on that we weren't a priority unless we were on television kicking a ball around. We ordered one app (why, I have no idea at this point), and our entrees which took around 50 minutes to arrive. Keep in mind that this is Indy500 weekend, and out-of-towners are slowly pouring into this place looking confused as where to sit, whom to see, or what to do. Almost utter chaos. Our food arrived, and it was very similar to anything you can get here in Atlanta at our chains like El Azteca, El Porton, or the like. Nothing spectacular. Nothing worth waiting over an hour to receive. I ate, because I'm fat, and I need to eat to fuel this chubby frame of mine, regardless of flavor.

Then comes getting the check. Almost 20 minutes after our plates were finished (read: not clean), we get the check. I scramble to find cash because who knows how long it's going to take to get my card swiped. Cash in hand, we escape from this mediocre experience with our sanity and this lovely review for would-be customers.

Again, I absolutely abhor writing these because I know someone's livelihood is affected by what I say. That BEING SAID, this place needs to adjust, staff, adjust some more, and maybe think about turning that giant television off when your livelihood is waiting for a water refill or just to order their dinners. Fountain Square is a lovely place to stop, walk around, and enjoy the city, but please spend your dollars elsewhere.

I cannot recommend Dr. Irby of Blossom Family Chiropractic in St. Petersburg enough!  

After having daily (and progressively worse) neck pain for years, I decided to try chiropractic care. Admittedly, I was a bit skeptical about the entire prospect, but Dr. Irby made me feel incredibly comfortable. She first did a thorough evaluation to determine the precise issues I had, and then laid out a comprehensive treatment plan. She took as much time as I needed to answer questions and was upfront about expectations and timetables for improvement. 

 After several weeks of treatment, my neck pain was all but gone. After several months, it was incredible to see the structural improvements in my neck via photos. I had taken several pounds of stress! It is one thing to feel better, but it's another entirely to see proof that the chiropractic care had improved my spinal health.

I could go on, but the bottom line is that if you are looking for a friendly, competent and caring Family Chiropractor, look no further!

We are on vacation and the excellent reviews convinced us to try this Italian restaurant away from the touristy part of Santa Barbara. It did not disappoint! Everything we tried was delicious. Spinach ravioli, gnocchi and bow ties with salmon in vodka sauce were outstanding. The staff was warm and attentive and made us feel welcome. Definitely a must try for Italian food in Santa Barbara.

The place isn't very big so it can get pretty busy.  Sat at the bar and the bartender acknowledge me very quickly but took a few minutes to get a drink.

To start, I ordered the beef empanadas, came with two and they were very good.  Excellent appetizer to start with and highly recommended.
For my entree I chose the enchiladas which were also excellent and very flavorful.  Just didn't last long enough on my plate.

The service is sometimes friendly, not very attentive, and not quick.  That being said, the food is exceptional.  The banchan (small sides) that comes with every meal is the best in Nashville, especially the boiled eggs with shredded beef.  The kimchi is crisp, clean, stinky, and delicious.  I can't even begin to say enough about the home made steamed dumplings, TRY THEM ASAP.

I've tried the following dishes and loved each one:

1. Grilled bulgogi (pork)
2. Kimchi stew with pork
3. Soft tofu stew with kimchi
4. Stir fried squid with noodles 
5. Beef & leek soup
6. Grilled beef short ribs

Seoul Garden is probably my 2nd-3rd favorite restaurant in Nashville.  The food is consistently good even though the service is somewhat shoddy.  It's also one of the only places in Nashville with bbq tables.

Ice cream daiquiri??? Yes.  All wonderful.  Great live music all day.  I did not eat here but other people food looked good.  Service was pretty crappy. Only 1 guy that was cheerful and any help. Rest of the staff just moped around.

It is safe to say I am obsessed with Oishi.

Their new location is beautiful, right down to the restrooms. Nice and clean.

The food was outstanding!  I absolutely love chicken and vegetable tempura and theirs was top notch.

The salad and gyoza appetizer were also delicious.

It wasn't even expensive for lunch.  I can't wait to return here and try more items from their menu.

Best brewery in Indy and Peyton is the best bartender!! Stopped by back in March en route to Louisville and came back this weekend while in town for a half marathon. Amazing beer, dog friendly, they donate 5% of their profit to animal rescue, plus fun live music venue with a BBQ food truck.

We decided to visit 2312 last night and turned out to be a disaster. We were meeting with some friends for some apps and drinks. The waitress Nichole was great and on top of everything. My friend felt a little ill and went into the bathroom,  when approached by the bar manager and asked to leave.  I was very confused by managers actions as my friend was not intoxicated and had done nothing wrong. Instead of asking my friend if he was ok or if maybe he would like to sit down and offer a water he continued to push us out the door.  This was handled in such a rude manner and was extremely embarrassing for my friend and i. This manager was the biggest jerk ive ever met,  i felt he was showing off to his friends.  We will not be visiting this establishment again.  To the manager id like to say grow up and get a life.

The atmosphere was very intimate , natural, trendy. 
Appetizers were our favorite.  With a table of eight mixed reviews, mostly positive. Highly recommend the Tuna.
Where to start? We come here twice a week and we LOVE the food, the owner, the sushi masters and the overall whole environment!! Super friendly to us and they have the best rolls in tampa!!

Awesome food and atmosphere. Came here looking for a good sports bar to watch a football game. Turned into a great decision. Great beer selection and large menu. Good wings and burgers with a variety of sauces. Also seems like they have plenty of good drink specials throughout the week. Will definitely be returning.

Went here on a Tuesday night to see Joe Jonas and DNCE, first visit ever. We did have to wait in line as others mention but it didn't take that long at all. Inside is just an open space. It's essentially a contest of who is the rudest person in the room. People shoving and stepping on you trying to get closer to the stage. If someone tall is in front of you, too bad, you can't see at all. And yes, it was hot. But my biggest grievance is that there was a tiny section carved out by the bar for 21+. Corralled into about 1/8th of the venue, we had to stay over there to drink. Luckily for us, this is where the giant poles are located. Was this just a thing for DNCE? The 21+ area was PACKED. So I am not the only "old lady" there!

ive eaten here twice and both times were great. the first time was during Restaurant Week several years ago. i was with a big group for loud girls and it was late. but the service was happy and fun and flirty. of course with a large group of young girls there is confusion, but it was all handled very well and with a "no big deal!" attitude, which i was thankful for. i'm veg so the waiter told me i could get anything i wanted made special for me. of course i just got some pasta and veggies, but it was really really good. cooked just right and very fresh. def an awesome evening. 
second time i went with 3 friends two summers ago. we all played dress-up and went for an early evening dinner. it wasnt crowded so they basically pampered us and entertained us. the food was great, nothing out of the ordinary, just good comfort food. the guys i went with loved it bc they were treated like kings, i think they even left like a 50% tip or something insane. 
if im in the mood for italian food (which im usually not haha) i would def go here for a  nice dinner.

With Bamboo being less than a minute drive from my home my wife and I eat here more than usual. My wife likes it quite a bit more than I. I prefer brown fried rice where she prefers the yellow rice that bamboo offers. I've had the Bourbon Chicken and the General Tso's. Both are good. My go-to is the General Tso combo with the yellow rice(fried rice). I usually get a side of Shrimp Lo Mein but we have recently discovered that they have Rice Noodles with Chicken. The Combo comes with an egg roll. Overall the food isn't bad. Like I said I just prefer a more authentic Chinese food experience. If my wife were writing this review it would be 5 stars.

Since COVID they do not offer indoor seating. You have to call ahead and when you arrive you look through the window where there is a table with orders sitting on it. You look to see if you order is on the table. If it is you enter the breezeway where they will cash you out if you have not paid yet. If you have paid they simply hand you your food through a partition and your in your way. The whole process is completely contactless. Very nice set up for those of you who are concerned with that.

Two words: chicken burrito
Get it. You'll be glad you did. No one in Nashville does it better than this place does.

Love this place. Great beer and delicious crawfish. The atmosphere is great. Great for crowds and fun (they have games to!) It's also kid friendly with a little section of tiny picnic benches, chalk and games. It's a big, opening, welcoming space. Tried the whiskey river (sour beer) and it was super yummy. I'll be back with friends.

My friends and I visit Chambers every few weeks for a weekday lunch.  Recently, we've noticed that their prices for lunch have gotten very high.  I don't eat meat, and previously one of my go-to dishes was a quinoa and roasted vegetable dish.  The price of that dish has now escalated to $15.  This is way too high for lunch, and also high for a dish consisting of a grain and some vegetables.  We are currently investigating our options for more reasonably-priced lunches in Doylestown.

Literally the WORST service i've had in my entire life. For your sake, don't sit at the bar. Actually just don't even go. I wish i knew what the two bartenders names were, but they didn't tell me. They also didn't smile or ask how we were doing. They were working at 3:00 on October 9th that's all i know. They looked like they hated their life and it slowly made me start to hate mine. SO ANYWAYS, the bartender hands me my beer and says "it's kind of warm" AND THEN WALKS AWAY!! so okay... that's not like horrible you know. Then we order a spinach dip and it took 40 minutes. When it came out it was water with artichokes and tomatoes in it. When they finally brought us the dip almost an hour later, they didn't even offer to comp it for us.... and then didn't even take our entree order. We tried to pay and leave but the bartenders only came to us every 25 minutes SO we left. I will never come here again and neither should anyone else. Like my god, it was fucking awful. It genuinely ruined my day.
So so so in love with Their cauliflower it's the best in town!! And I always order a bottle of wine to pair with
We have been customers since their opening. Always have fresh muffins and coffee. I love the bagels.

Just stay away! We walked in everything feels greasy including the floor, you stick to it. Then the waitress an older lady with white hair was very rude and sat 2 tables down to take our order, very strange. You don't know whether to sit down or order at desk. They have a board menu or menus at the table. They keep telling you to read the board it explains the food better. I ordered the burger you pay extra for any condiments and fries . Food was very greasy and made me sick for hours.
The pizza is delicious. Unlike some other reviewers, I have never had any problems with wait times or the quality of the food. I normally order online and the pizza is always ready on time.

Received gel nail service at this location for the first time last weekend and the guy did a really good job! He added a design that is the best! But Instead of the gel peeling off a week later, it chipped off. They say the gel should last 2 weeks. Not in this case. I've had the same service done at a place closer to my home and the gel would peel right off within a week! So this isn't all that bad. 

I would return again next time I'm in the area and let them know what happened on my last visit. Hopefully they will do a better job.

Food was so amazing! But this was the worst service I've experienced in a long time. The service ruined a good and expensive meal. We would of gotten more drinks, tapas and desserts but were not asked once if we were okay or wanted more. A few feet from us the other server was at the bar offering customers discounted bottles of wine, however we were not asked if we wanted another drink. Very bad and unprofessional. Too bad because we had high hopes of making this a frequent restaurant as we live very close to it.

The food is fantastic.... The setting is fun and the staff is outstanding... I have had at least 100 bowls made so many different ways, family outings, or just with friends...
Awesome place to eat and have drinks...
When you go with Genghis Grill, you're going with quality and freshness and you gotta love that...
Thank you for all the Great times and Great service and Great food..
Everyone that works here have attitudes and talk to you with a tone like you're bothering them and stupid. They obviously hate their job and/or life. But I guess that's the norm for the dmv.

This is one of my favorite BYOB places in philly! 
We did the prefix menu on sunday twice. We came back for our 2nd year anniversary. I really love this place, the menu is well made. if you are into seafood then you will love this place! every dish is like a surprise!
The prefix was $30 per person, but it is worth the money since it's BYOB. 
It is a very cozy restaurant, it sits about 20 people.

The Eagle restaurant at 310 Massachusetts Ave, Indianapolis, Indiana is just absolutely incredible.

This truly comes from someone who grew up in the South, with North and South Carolina cuisine in my blood and dining room each and every night.  I have never had a meal at a mainstream, hip, restaurant that claimed to have Soul Food as the menu and actually nailed it.  The Eagle does an exceptional job at providing a well-rounded soul food menu, with several local beers on tap, a great wine list, and desserts.  This place is Hip and Very Good.  It's a really cool combination.

It's all in the Fried Chicken.  Choose from Whole Chicken, 1/2 Chicken, 1/4 Chicken White Meat, or 1/4 Chicken Dark Meat.  

The sides are just amazing, perfectly sized portions, of goodness.  Pick from FRIES (tossed in herbs with a side of aioli), COLLARDS (stewed with ham hocks & bacon), COLE SLAW (creamy & a little tart), SPOONBREAD (iron skillet corn bread with maple butter), SWEET POTATO CROCK (with toasted mini marshmallows), MAC & CHEESE (five cheeses & garlic breadcrumbs), or WHITE CHEDDAR GRITS (with house made pickled peppers).  We tried just about all of them and let me say they really are very delicious.

Salads, Snacks, and Sandwiches are all on the menu too.

Remember, the Beer bottles, Beer cans, Beer on Tap, and Wine selection is pretty great as well.  We just cannot find anything wrong with The Eagle.  It was by far our best meal in Indianapolis during our 4-day stay.

Service too is on point.  Nate is incredible.  He nailed our order exactly right (down to every detail) the first time, checked in regularly with us, had a genuine interest in how everyone at the table was doing, and was just an all-around nice guy.  Thank You Nate!

If you haven't visit The Eagle restaurant at 310 Massachusetts Ave, Indianapolis, Indiana, you really are missing out.  Shame on you.

I have been a client for 15 years and was reminded today of why I had moved to morning only appointments.  After an hour and a half past my appointment time had passed with no courtesy mention of we are running behind, I started asking staff about my appointment.  After a few inquiries, my unapologetic doctor finally appeared.  No common courtesy.  "Hey, we are really sorry."  Actually, no apologies at all.  This is not Covid related, this has happened several times before Covid.  So, if you don't need to take off work to go to your appointment and half a day to spend there, go for it!

On my day off, decided to go check out one of  Jose Garces' restaurants for lunch during Philly Restaurant week. $20 for a 3 course lunch.

The decor has an open space area reminiscent of a loft with a monochromatic color palette. Subway tiles accent the walls and columns throughout the space which gives it an upscale terminal/market vibe. Light fixtures are a mix of recess, track, and two styles of industrial wrought iron pendant lights.

An adjoining wine shop with a vast selection of reds & whites from across the globe. As well as specialty tasting olive oil and vinegar bar.

The only negative is that there is  one bathroom for men & women and there was a steady line throughout our visit.

The food was excellent. The Spaniard sandwich was flavorful and filling. The grilled chicken was tender and succulent. The bread was similiar to Challah with a firm yet fluffy texture. The accompanying condiments of applewood bacon, roma tomatoes and romesco aioli subtly complimented the chicken with sweet and tart flavors fusing together. Mouth FIREWORKS !!!! The homemade chips made me want a whole bag due to the slightly crispy, dark yet lightness. (Reminded me of old school Wise potato chips).

Due to a stuffed tummy, the desserts were packed to go. Macoroons and a marscapone, huckleberry cake. Presentation of the cake in a round shot size glass was special in a simple and "fru fru" way.

I agree with all the reviews on this page THE BEST PLACE TO BUY ZEPS IN NORRISTOWN but have one complaint.  I live about 20 miles away so when I come to Eves I usually get between $100 & $200 worth of sandwich's.  If you order hot peppers on your sandwich's they are FREE.  If you ask for 2 small side orders of hot peppers for those who like to put their own peppers on THEY CHARGE YOU $.70 CENTS EXTRA ? BUT IF YOU GET THEM ON THE SANDWICH THEY ARE FREE.  SO TODAY EVEN THOUGHT MY ORDER WAS OVER $120.00 TOTAL, THEY LOST THE SALE OF TWO MORE LARGE ZEPS FOR A TOTAL OF $22.00 BECAUSE THEY WANTED .35 CENTS A CUP FOR PEPPERS ?  Does this make sense to you as a business you would rather lose $22.00 in sandwich's  and charge .70 cents for peppers you would put on for FREE ?????????? I used to spend between $1,800 to $2,200 a year at Eves but in 2017 it will be many trips less over peppers you should get for free!  I ask the cashier who run the business and she told me the kids were. The oldest daughter who took care of my orders for years knew what I spend at their business and always gave a bag of chips or a 2 liter bottle of soda with orders between $100 & $200 dollars and now they can't afford two .35 cents cups of peppers.  NOT GOOD FOR BUSINESS ----Maybe you should look back and take some advice from your sister who knew what running a good business was like.

I want to like Foam more.  I really do.

I want to steal some of their decor.  It has a pretty good vibe.

I am not a coffee drinker, but I love chai.  Their chai was watered down and flavorless.  My partner said her coffee was less than good.

One amazing drink I tried:  Summer Bourbon Smash.  Bourbon, strawberries, and balsamic vinegar.  Probably one of the best drinks I've ever had.  It was tiny for $7.50, but I enjoyed every last drop.  

If friends are going, I'd probably go back.  Maybe it will grow on me.

I don't really understand the draw of Chik-fil-A with all of the lines waiting for a chicken sandwich.  With that said, I have had great experiences with the food, services, and professionalism of the business.  The Chik-fil-A sauce brings my friends back...  All-in-all it was a very positive experience

Classic big business poorly run.  They scheduled an appointment and decided to cancel it without letting me know.  Problem is that I waited around for 2 hours before I got anxious enough to check in.  Immediately ignored their mistake and tried to reschedule me for another day.  Not gonna happen- take your business elsewhere, just like I did.

I'm going to admit it, I devoured my dog before taking pics but that should tell you just how good these babies are!

These aren't your average Oscar Myer weiners my friends, these are gourmet dogs done to the max.

I opted for the SB style hot dog that had fresh avocado slices, OMG that sucker was awesome, and my buddy Jim had the Western Dog that had oodles of bacon garnished on top with a BBQ sauce, it looked amazing and for someone who said he wasn't hungry it was gone pretty fast.

The guys running this stand are just as awesome, super friendly and fun to converse with, don't be shy start a convo with them, they like feedback.

Grab a beer at the market, head on over and get a gourmet dog and have a few laughs, heck you might even find yourself posing for pics with the owners.

On a side note I'm pretty sure I'm still a bit drunk after all the festivities last night. Lol

I have never been disappointed with the flowers, service and the delivery.  I have both received and sent flowers from here and never had a complaint.  I will continue to use them as always..
My husband and I celebrated our anniversary on Sept 12th and received a beautiful floral arrangement from our kids and grand kids.  The reason for this update is because I just was so happy with how well they held up!!  New blooms opened and gave us continued pleasure.

The Korean BBQ short ribs and Duck are my two favorite meals.  The rolls are good but I would stay away from the "special" rolls, not that special.  The calamari is a great appetizer.

If you don't want the "jerky waiter" ask to sit on the left side, he has always served on the right side.
Anthony Wayne theater is great their is no problems with anything and they get a bad wrap but they really are a great theater that deserves a better reputation.

First time here, atmosphere was cozy,  friendly,  upscale, pleasantly busy. The food was some of the best I've had. Chilean sea bass was amazing,  perfectly crisp on the outside, butterlike but firm on the inside, light lemon flavor, I loved it!  Must have for dessert, chef's bread pudding, delicious,  delicate,  perfect with coffee. I will be back to try everything on the menu!
It honestly feels like me and my family go here every week... Service is great though. The managers are really nice and the food is delicious. The tempura banana dessert is AMAZING.

This was my first visit but will not be my last. We had the octopus appetizer which was outstanding. Both entrees were amazing. Our waiter was attentive and very knowledgable about each dish. His recommendations were excellent. I can't wait to return!

Saw the commercial for this place and decided to try it on our girl's day out. The view of the water and the service are very good.  The food, on the other hand, is pricey and mediocre. The price is not the issue, it is the taste of the food. What a disappointment. I will not return.

the stylist i go to when i am chop shop bound deserves 4.5 stars on her own, but since this supposed to be cumulative, wellll......it gets 3. whenever i would go in, without picking out a stylist, i would come out occasionally....well, pretty grumpy.

now?? i go for audrey. she's awesome possum, and is a fantastic colourist. woot to her!!!

The consistency of the noodles on the drunken noodles was absolutely awful, Pretty much goop, either soaked too long or over cooked. Wasn't a huge fan of the big pieces of cabbage either. The meat was ok and the spice level was ok, but it was hard to get passed the noodles which are half of the dish.

I actually really enjoyed the crab wontons. Fresh green onions are a nice touch and the emphasis is on the filling instead of the fried breading.

The salad rolls were ok. The rolls themselves come wth shrimp and chicken and seem pretty fresh. It comes with sweet and sour sauce which is weird, but also with normal peanut sauce. The peanut sauce was a bit coagulated, but the flavor wasn't bad.

I would try somewhere else before I came back.
We had the thai tea and taro-flavored bubble teas, which tasted great! Planning to return soon for the food

..... it's the helpless employees for me. Came in looking for a desk and we were told they had NONE. So another employee snaps and says show them the one by the bathroom. Well this was a huge console/entertainment system. Not a desk. So we said ok thanks we will walk around and look. And what do you know. 5-6 furniture pieces labeled DESK. Lol what a joke this place is. Even if we found a desk we wanted we wouldn't have bought it here for the lack of effort and help we wished we received. Best of luck to this business but don't go in thinking you're going to get willing to help employees

We chose this restaurant for dinner because it was literally a few steps away from the hotel we were staying at.  We had just come in from a 7 hour drive and really didn't want to drive anymore.  It's atmosphere is basically no-frills but we had no complaints about the food.  Many of the dishes are offered in smaller portions which is perfect for my appetite.  They also had spaghetti carbonara which isn't often found at Italian restaurants in smaller metro areas.  

Their specialty seemed to be pizza and they boast about have a 40 in pizza.  So if you are really hungry and want pizza you might want to give this place a try.

Not the typical "fluff and buff" spa. I was very pleased to find this slightly off the beaten path massage center. The massage was tailored to my needs and requests at just the right pressure. As a long distance runner I have had many massage experiences and this rates in the top 10 for me! 

I highly recommend this center if you are looking for a therapeutic massage

Dave

Epic amazing place to eat. I travel for a living and go to many places. This place was incredible. I would give it 10 stars if I could. Great menu. Lots of food. Lots of variety. And fantastic quality.

Coffee and cappuccino were good and service was great.  Plenty of open tables even during a holiday week where we heard them remark they were busier than a normal weekday.  We weren't terribly impressed with the food.  We ordered a mexi from the specials and while the lime sour cream was very good, the rest was average and it came with stale tortilla chips on the side rather than the advertised fried corn tortillas that it was supposed to be layered on.  We also had the pumpkin pancake pies which were really just pumpkin pancakes with a whole bunch of mix ins.  They were good but not what we expected from the description.  Cup of fruit had a hash brown mixed into it and quite a bit of very underripe melon, but the berries were good.

The prices are super expensive for the quantity and quality. I had chicken Biryani that was served in a small bowl and its definitely not chicken Biryani. it was just rice mixed in chicken curry. 

There is only one person who takes order, serves food and does everything, and he seems to be a jerk. very rude and he was chewing tobaco which working. The place is not very clean either. I am just sure how this place has got 4 stars. 

I just feel sorry for the people(incl me) who visited this place since they could not find a better place for indian food.
Great meal, good service  and laid back atmosphere.

Perfect place for the ultimate soul food! Breakfast until 11 am on Sunday but had the best Southern grub reminiscent of grandma's Mississippi farm meal! Fried chicken, roast with carrots and potatoes, greens, catfish, pork, Mac n cheese, creamed corn, slaw, broccoli salad, corn bread, rolls, green beans! Ugh, get me a wheel Barrel! So good... oh, a scrumptious piece of Pee-can Pie! Don't forget the fresh peach preserves for your roll! Gonna come back again for breakfast!!

I don't like the fact that after you eat here you smell like a Fried fish...the Exhaust should be checked clean or change...My hair smells like a deep fried hair lol....Food wise is 4 star...Service 3 star. Their sides Is 5 stars Galic Stew, Bread Pudding,Corn Bread...
Got a chrome set that was sooo beautiful it was the best i have ever seem and excellent service

Decided to try this after reading the menu online. We were seated quickly and greeted by a friendly face. After one hour, we still had not received any food. Perhaps the menu is a work of fiction as those around us waited hopelessly as well. I challenge the management to figure out what is wrong, or to simply close the location. After all, how long does it take to prepare an egg or waffle??

HORRIBLE  EXPERIENCE 

If only "Zero Star" was an option, that would be undeserving.

My first time getting up, prior to my manicure completion, and just accepting a $10 waste of money.

It was unbelievable!  Not only did the nail tech incompetently perform my service, the unprofessionalism was appalling.

Not only did we sit at a work station without a barrier, but she continued to have a "speaker phone" conversation while doing my manicure. If this wasn't rude enough, her male associate brought her a second phone that she temporarily engaged in a second conversation. 

During this ordeal, which lasted long enough to clip my nails, poorly trim my cuticles and bloody my finger, she began to put lotion on my arm without even smoothing my nails with a file.

But this wasn't even the worst part for me. She pulled her mask down to ensure the other party of her conversation could hear her better. This resulted in my turning my head to insulate myself from her mask-less conversation. After a couple minutes, I had to get up. 

With the virus ravaging our way of life, this tech felt it was ok to work without a mask for significant time. Needless to say, "her business was more important than my business." She didn't get the hint that her customer's head was turned away. 

She was in disbelief that I didn't want to finish. Unfortunately, I used some regrettable choice words prior to asking her what I owed. I was charged $10 bucks. I was hesitant to pay, but I guess this is how they do business.

I took these pictures prior to applying peroxide and neosporin at a friend's home in the neighborhood.

One of my all time best retail experiences! I thought maybe, I would be able to find a few gifts for Christmas and my mom asked me along to one of her favorite spots. They were so pleasant, so helpful, and never in that overbearing way. I found everything I needed for my shopping. They do a great job of making you feel at home. In fact, I was eyeing a beautiful bag for myself but I'm not shopping for me so I walked away and apparently as soon as I left, they set it aside just in case (they knew) I would be back for it! The point is, if you're still looking for gifts, head on over to Irvington. The Black Sheep has all the cool stuff without the marked up novelty shop price tags. I'm a lifer now. Thank you for being so awesome!!!!

Omg..  if you are stopped up then just take a deep breath in and you will be good to go or have a sneezing fit... but it's all good.
Penzys has every single spice or Extract you can think of.
You are able to smell everyone of them as well as get a description of what you can you the spice for.
If you are a new Customer and sign up with your email address you get a Free Cocoa Spice!!!
This is a cute shop on the main drag of Maplewood.
Great pizza, big size slices. Amazing garlic knots. Staff is friendly. Affordable. What more can I say. Go there is you're hungry!

Uber eats delivered us our first taste of Yats today. I can say, with great confidence, it will not be our last! Yummy! We both chose 1/2 entrees and loved them all but the Jambalaya. It didn't  hold up to the Maque Choux, (the fave!) Drunken Chicken and Red Beans with Smoked Sausage. Yummy bread was included that was warmed with some sort of seasoning. Delicious!

The best spot for brunch in Nashville. We arrived around 10:15am on a Saturday (the Tavern opened at 10am) and the wait was about 30 minutes for a party of 2. We were sat at the bar and appropriately socially distanced from other guests.

You can't beat the 2 for 1 drink specials. I had the blood orange mimosas (delicious!) and my friend had the Bellini sparkle, which was good but definitely on the sweeter side.

We split the fries with garlic aioli to start. Super crispy and tasty. My friend had the red velvet waffle, which she enjoyed. I had the Singapore stir fry, which was good, but I definitely would try something different next time. 

Overall, a good experience and cool vibe.

We love NaBrasa. We go for all our celebrations now. The swordfish was amazing and we love that they add items to their menu. The drink menu is awesome as it gives so many options to those who drink. Staff is really down to earth and kind. Not all expensive places need a stuffy atmosphere and that's what we love. We like to be candid and have fun.

Really nice car wash and the best Mister Car wash in the area compared to the other ones around Tampa. Their hand drying isn't the greatest, they usually miss a spot or two, but you can't beat only $29.99 for unlimited platinum washes every month! The tire shine and the coats of soaps and protect ants are great on my car (2017 Camaro). At first I was honestly skeptical over automated washes, but I've seen even a Mercedes AMG GT go through the wash and that car is over a $100,000 haha. I used to pay $25-$30 for a single car wash back in NY, and the fact that I can get unlimited a month for that price is awesome.

I am not a big fan of falafel sandwich until I tried this place and since then whenever I am craving for a good falafel sandwich this is the place I go for. I have tried the eggplant sandwich, Latke vegetarian sandwich, falafel sandwich and I have not been disappointed with any of it.  The taste is consistent and I think it is well priced. My fav one is Latke vegetarian sandwich that has a veggie patty as well as falafel. Its pretty filling for me and I sometimes add side of french fries (its hot, fresh but a little oily for me) to it. I really like to get pickle and jalapeño from the salad bar...gives good taste to the sandwich. 
If you have a party and need quick bites I would recommend ordering their falafel platter... I believe it is $20-$30 and get plenty of falafels for a small group of ~15.

Excellent service. Delicious meaty food. My friend had the rabbit & dumplings, I had the cochon, and we shared the pork cheeks. They were all flavorful with tender meat. The restaurant was over air-conditioned, but that seemed common in many buildings during our visit in late September.

I'm split when it comes to the rating for this restaurant. Came here for lunch on 12/26 and was a little early for our reservation however was seated promptly by the hostess and soon after greeter by a waiter for our drinks and followed by another waiter for our food order. 

So mind you I had just come from eating beignets at cafe du monde and pretty stuffed from the delicious pastries. 

I ordered the gumbo and bf ordered the roast beef Po boy. Gumbo tasted right and was good. The bf really liked his enormous Po boy however I didn't really love the roast beef when I tried it. The fries were ok...perhaps a little overdone. We also had the bread pudding dessert which tasted delicious but was super sweet! I believe it is intended to be that way as it is traditional and customary for the dish. Could not finish that one since I was stuffed and on the brink of food induced diabetes.

Service was excellent - 5
Location and ambience was lovely - 5
Food so so but I wouldn't come back again - 3

Since a restaurant is first and foremost about food I have to dock the stars since I wasn't a fan unlike many other yelpers. Such a cute location and inside is full of history.

Amazing!!!!  The staff is awesome, food incredible, and the atmosphere is very comfortable. I got the shrimp and grits and it was wonderful!  A must go in New Orleans. It's $$. But totally worth it!  

PS-Eat dessert at another place. We shared the apple cobbler and it was just so,so.
Best authentic Mexican food around! Owner is always friendly even when they're busy. I highly recommend this restaurant.

Forget the 2 ladies that helped me out taking links off my watch, there was a family that took a bit of time ahead of me, she said I was waiting a while and did the service for free, offered that first thing when we spoke, was very very nice. Good conversation with genuine people happy first experience at this place

Roy is extremely professional. He examined my washer, showed me what was happening and together we decided I needed a new washer. He gave me his opinion of the best brand to purchase. He charged a very fair service charge. I highly recommend Roy to service your appliances.
Pam M , June 3, 2020

FrontPoint makes it very difficult to cancel.  I've been trying to cancel my account for the past 6 months.  I had been a customer for more than 2 years and had fulfilled all of my contract obligations.  When I spoke to a representative about cancelling, he tried to get me to stay by offering me discounted pricing on my monitoring service. I was NOT interested because I had already switched to Ring which offered significantly better hardware (supports multiple keypads) for a fraction of the price of what I was paying with FrontPoint.  Finally after hearing all of the incentives and declining all of them, I was told that I needed to submit in writing a 30 day cancellation notice and was given an email address.  I submitted an email stating my name and the account that I wished to cancel.  A few months went by, and I noticed that my credit card was still being charged even after 30 days from my cancellation notice.  

I called FrontPoint again, but was unable to get a hold of the right person who was needed for this type of situation.  I then decided to cancel my credit card, because FrontPoint does not have a way to remove an active credit card that is associated to a subscription.  No where on FrontPoint's website is there an email address to contact someone for billing or even support.  

After a couple months, I received a call from a FrontPoint representative informing me that my credit card information needed to be updated.  I informed the representative that I had canceled my account months ago and that FrontPoint is no longer authorized to charge my credit card.  The representative stated that he would make a note of this to my file.  After the call, I thought finally I was done with FrontPoint.  A couple weeks went by, and I received an automated phone call from FrontPoint stating that important information needed to be updated to my account.  I have been receiving these annoying calls everyday now for the  past 3 months.  Not sure what to do to get FrontPoint to stop.  

Finally today, a representative called me and stated that I have an outstanding balance.  I corrected him and told him that I cancelled months ago, and that FrontPoint has overcharged my account for the time after I cancelled, and that I was entitled to a refund.  He said he would look into the matter, but I doubt it, and I asked him to cancel my account.

I find it very disappointing that FrontPoint makes it so easy to sign-up, but extremely difficult (if not impossible) to cancel. The fact that FrontPoint has to stoop so low to try to retain a customer makes me feel obligated to warn others about this.

I came here to see Train Wreck with my friends. We were all really excited to be at a dine and watch movies place. When we first entered, we went in with to the ticket person with our pre purchased tix and her attitude and body language screamed 'I don't wanna be here/hate my job' which was a bummer. It really killed the excitement we had for this place.

We ended up having to wait so we went to the restaurant section of the theater which was clean. It was a little too dark and I don't know if it was on purpose of their just trying to save on electricity. 

When we entered the theater it was an average movie threaten size but with bigger seats and attached tables. I ordered the nachos as an app with my friend and they were good. The cheese sauce was good but there weren't enough toppings. For an entree I order, pasta and meatballs, and there was an over powering amount of cheese on the meat balls so I didn't eat them. I just ate the pasta. I would recommend not anything with the cilantro. It has a processed taste to it. I didn't know that cilantro could have a processed taste to it until I had that meal. It had an unpleasant taste and you can't really avoid it. 

Overall, the service was okay but I didn't like the food AT ALL.
Favorite burger place ever!! The staff the food especially the milkshakes! One of the managers Emily was so nice and professional! I'll forever recommend this place.

I don't know who sells you  your 12 packs of Pabst, but I go out of my way to buy mine form Cosimo Matassa.  For those that don't know, Cosimo was the owner of recording studios that basically recorded every New Orleans R&B hit from the end of the 40's all the way through to the 1970's, and he engineered them all himself.

Professor Longhair, Fats Domino, Ernie K Doe,  Lloyd Price, Jerry Lee Lewis, Little Richard all were recorded by Cosimo.  He recorded Roy Brown's Good Rockin Tonight before there was even a tape recorder in New Orleans...1 take...direct to acetate...and after retiring he from music and at 85 years old,  he is still at his families market.  Not everyday, but he's around.  The day before Hurricane Gustav, we was behind the counter selling us our liquor.

Rouses may have a better selection and cheaper prices, but did the cashier get to ogle Irma Thomas when she was still  young and very hot?  I want to be looked at by the eyes thast looked at her.

Oh, and they sell plate lunches too.

I got the tongs burrito and my wife got the soft tacos. Both were superb and full of flavor. I would recommend the burrito if you are a little hungrier. The mix of the Mexican rice with the sour cream was amazing. The ensalada verde salsa was paired nicel as well. Can't wait to try the lomo and the oven roasted chicken!
Fattahs great...always cuts it right and for an affordable price . Don't waste your money at other spots...fattah hooks it up

Not happy... I spent $100 plus for detailing.
My car came back not clean as I expected. There is still dust on interior that I can see, windows are still dirty. I pay extra to remove stain on carpet, didn't get remove or even  fade.

I will go somewhere people will pay attention to detail.
I waste a lot of money.

Just a few thoughts regarding the quality of the food before I start on the quality of service: I've certainly had better Indian cuisine. This was nothing write home about. Average buffet setup with a limited selection. If I had to point out two highlights of the meal, it was the Mango Lassi and the Chicken Curry. Those were probably two of the only things worth consuming. The Naan was unusually dry and broke apart. There were chips of bone inner mixed in the Mutton that someone could have potentially chipped a tooth on if not careful. The fried cheese ball soaked in sugar and honey was beyond sickening sweet. The rice was crunchy, obviously not cooked thoroughly. Most of the cuisine was very heavy on the stomach to the point of nauseous, making for a very uncomfortable rest of the afternoon.  

The quality of service was less than to be desired. Instead of being greeted and lead to our seat when we first arrived, a man came out from the kitchen and pointed to where we were to sit. After disappearing the back for about five minutes, he came out with residue spotted silverware and a pitcher of water. There was no greeting offered, no inquiry if we had been here before. He quickly filled the glasses and left. (Not to mention this would be the LAST time we would get our glasses filled.) We observed our surrounding environment, noticing others who appeared to be regulars helping their selves to the buffet, so we followed suit. 
One of the bullet points on the buffet etiquette list at the beginning of the line was to always take a clean plate if returning to the buffet. Good thing we weren't hungry when we arrived there, because we probably would have created the leaning tower of plates! None of the wait staff returned to collect the dirty dishes, NOR was there a place to leave the dirty ones behind!  When it came time to pay the bill, the gentleman at the front promptly stated the amount.  He took the exact change and said nothing as we thanked him upon leaving. Not even a "Thank-you"' "Come back again" or even, "Get the hell out". Nothing. 

Overall rude wait staff and mediocre food provides for a poor dining experience. I'm not sure who in their right mind would nominate them for a readers choice award in both 2004 & 2006. I'm also confused by the 4 and 5 star reviews others have given this place. Perhaps I came on a bad day? Maybe everyone got yelled at in the kitchen before we arrived? Perhaps I wore the wrong color? Who knows! All I can say is I'm convinced I would have had a better dining experience along the side of the Schuylkill Expressway, gagging on exhaust and flying debris than I did here.

Overall this was great. 
We got seated right away which was great even though it was busy. 
Our waiter was great and friendly he even tried to convince my seafood hating wife to try the crab cakes.  Even though she didn't. 
The food was great my only complaint was how long we waited for our entrees. The starters came out quick but we waited almost another 30 minutes after that for the entrees.
Alex the salesperson is great. He started helping us look for a new vehicle. Still looking though!
I really enjoy ending my weekend with a relaxing community Yin class at Embarque. I brought the BF along once, and now he asks to go with me every week.

Food was amazing. They were happy to accommodate my vegetarian diet subbing a portobello mushroom for the meat patty. My son ordered a regular burger and scarfed it down. Very happy with the service. The parking situation could be better, you have to park in a tiny parking garage. We will be back though.

Great atmosphere,  staff is awesome!!!!!!
Adult time or perfect family dining.   Sit inside or out lake side

OK I split the difference and gave 3 stars.  here's why:

Food selection - 5 stars
Beer selection - 5 stars
Food quality - 4 stars
Service - 1 star
Prices - 1 star - soooooo expensive!
Cashiers are rude and inconsiderate.

I dropped over $50 on random groceries and they rang it up incorrectly and swiped my card.  They then asked me to pay for the 2 items they forgot to ring up in cash.

It was a nightmare.  I basically spent $54 on a dozen eggs, an apple, an orange, a bowl of cut fruit, a chef salad, a turkey wrap, some hummus, a quart of OJ, 2 boxes of raspberries, a container of mixed nuts, a container of dried apricots, a package of sliced organic cheese.

$54!  Ack!!!!!  For one small bag of groceries.

That said - I am glad they were there when I needed them.  I paid the price for the convenience.  And for organic.

I found Jason's on Yelp while traveling on business from Houston. The experience was so great that I came back for dinner the next evening. While the space is very small, the sushi is fantastic, everything is fresh and very well prepared. Not to mention that everyone is very accommodating and kind. This restaurant really is a gem, I love to see small family businesses like this that really care about quality and service.

I was not prepared for just how amazing this place is. My friend warned me but I expected mostly fresh produce and meat stands like I guess, not the culinary hodgepodge that this place was. This was one of my favorite places in Philly. They have every cuisine imaginable. I wish I had one more day to my trip to eat my way through the market. I unfortunately didn't get to try a whole lot because I couldn't get past the cheese steaks! This place is a true gem and no tourist should miss it. So happy it was across the street from my hotel.

Longs is a serious doughnut place. Bring cash, except to wait in line no matter what day or time. They are that good. This past Saturday we didn't get there till 11 and the line was out the door and almost to 16th Street. It really didn't take that long to get in the door and luckily they still had a ton of doughnuts, cakes, and other goodies left. A lot of places run out early, but we've never walked around empty handed, quite the opposite actually. The yeast at 11 were HOT and fresh and they melt in your mouth. The cinnamon fired and nut ones are always good. The long johns are so out of this world and filled with a ton of cream. They actually pack each one full to the brim of creamy goodness.
Great fun atmosphere.  Great food and reasonably priced. Lots for your money. Televisions for sports and a great relaxed feeling. Lots of daily specials and always a satisfying time.

Jambalaya was subpar and not worth eating. I made a complaint after trying to eat even just the sausage and they told me they couldn't do anything.  Not the level of service or quality of taste I expected and I won't be visiting again.

Disappointed about the miscommunication between the person ringing me up and the cooks. My food was done, just was missing 1 thing. He didn't relay the message. I waited almost 10 mins before someone finally asked what I was waiting on, and then JUST threw it in the oven. I left with cold food. 

Otherwise, the food was okay. I'm willing to go back and give them another try. Despite the food being cold, it was still better than others.

The food was great. Ramen was one of the best I've had. Came with my whole family for a birthday for the first time, we all enjoyed the food. 

But my reasoning for a 2 star- the service. It was TERRIBLE. They were inattentive, the waitress seemed distracted. Didn't give us table settings, utensils, the waitress didn't give us her name. The waitress seemed so dry, not friendly, or give us one smile and only checked up on us when we called her over. I did not feel welcomed at all. Took her about 15 minutes to get us drinks. The food took an hour to get to us. We were missing food. All around we hated the service. Again, food was great and the service sucked.  Customer service is very important. For that reason we won't go back.

I received an ad in the mail.  It says "$9.90 per month, no gimmicks". I thought that's a great deal so I stopped by during lunch break to check it out.  Salesman told me there's a $199 sign up fee plus $35 per year for maintenance.  Sounds like gimmicks to me.

We sat in the Hardee's Granite City IL drive thru for 14 minutes today. When our cold order finally made it to our car, our fries were not in the bag. When we got home, we learned that although we requested no mayo, both burgers had mayo! What was taking so long because it sure wasn't preparing hot food or ensuring order accuracy.

We started out with the wood fired mushrooms and dates... Immediately blown away. Macy served us - ask for her - she made amazing suggestions. Zeke had the special and I had the chicken dish. Neither disappointed. Full of flavor and very original. For dessert, the orange cake was PHENOMENAL!! Add live music, you've won my heart Union 50. I would definitely come back.

I've been bringing my dog Sully here almost a full year since he was a puppy and he loves it! He has separation anxiety, but has never had an issue going to day camp. He's always so excited to greet the employees and comes home tired and happy every time! The groomers always do a great job trimming his nails too. 

Thank you guys for always taking such good care of my baby.

TINA TINA TINA!!!!  Can't say enough good things about this girl.  She found a spot for 12 organ grinders after a parade and treated us like QUEENS!  Everything from mass drink orders to apps in seconds, to splitting checks like it wasn't a giant pain in the ass.  Tina took such great care of us with style and a smile, we will for sure be back to see her and you should too!!!

So good - Amin (sp?) is fantastic.  

We live right near this little gem and frequent often.  Good, inexpensive pizza in Philly is hard to find - 


good thing there's Mamma Mia...

Definitely one of my favorites when I travel to Indy for work! My favorite are the fish tacos (yes, lettuce wraps) and really any of the veggies. Just tried the tomato soup and it was perfection. So many things I wanted to try on the menu this time, I almost went back for dinner after having lunch there! Service is always friendly, not a bad thing to say about this spot.
I had a wonderful experience here.  We sat outside on the patio and there were fire pits lit, great atmosphere. The food was delicious.  I will definitely go back soon.
Fast and professional service. Thankfully they had time slots open during the busy spring break but timeframe, even gave me some extra time. Affordable and convenient

Nicest, cleanest and most professional nail salon I've ever been in. I had the Spa Pedicure with gel polish and left feeling like a Princess! Mai did a perfect pedicure! The spa is immaculately clean, all utensils sanitized and the staff was very friendly and professional. I highly recommend this place to anyone!!

A cookie cutter, hole in the wall, Chinese restaurant. They're all the same. They all use the same menu printed in grean and red ink and just change the restaurant name at the top...
