No surprises, except when I walked in to get my order, the Chinese children sitting at a table (I'm assuming they're the owner's kids) weren't eating Chinese food but rather McDonalds. What does that say about what they're offering? It was just okay. I've had better. I've had worse.
Go to the Holistic Connection down the street.  Get a brownie and eat it.  Go straight to Best Day and get a 60 min foot reflexology.  You are welcome.

Will never go back. The customer service I received was so poor. The sandwich was dry and flavorless. Go to Geno's across the street. Better service better taste! And to the man at the counter, just a reminder I'm the customer, you better get that attitude and wipe it off your face at the window. You don't talk to me the customer like I'm an idiot and start yelling how to form a line and then yell out next means who's up next to order a sandwich. As the customer we pay your bills and make you rich and by the look of it Geno's line pisses all over your line. There was no line to form because no one was on it. You work so fast you don't even know how to properly wrap the sandwich never mind put it in a bag. Your business should be embarrassed.

The food here is exceptionally prepared. The brisket is phenomenal. The brussel sprouts with cashews were perfectly cooked and seasoned. The service was good, a little bit over the top in trying to be too cool. But the atmosphere, while very busy, still left you capable of sharing an intimate experience with a date.
Will definitely go again and again.

We have dined at Arch Rock several times and the experience has alway been good. Today I had the cioppino was excellent but my wife had the fish and chip and both the fish and frustrating were soggy. She has had them on a prior visit and they were perfect.

The truth is I would give 4 stars for the food and a zero for the service. I really feel bad writing this during Covid as I make a point to support our local restaurants and businesses during this difficult time. My friend and I are nurses, also working hard. We finally made it out for a noon lunch to have a break. After finishing our meal, and still sipping my drink, our waitress approached the table and asked us to leave because she said there was another reservation waiting. I could understand if we had been there for an extended amount of time. We were there a total of 53 minutes. Although I enjoy the food and location, I sadly won't be coming back. I have NEVER in my life been asked to leave a restaurant. It was incredibly humiliating and unprofessional. I want to know if management finds this acceptable?

Just went there yesterday,. the manager who is power tripping ---asked me if i was on drugs, then talked shit to me, then got me a beer, cut my hair for free, and wondered why his bitch ass got no tip.  run your lip--get no tip.  duh !  I'm not the nicest person in the world but I know how to respect people, obviously as  you can tell by this yelp post--all up in here.  they got plenty of attitude fo sho!

Simply great.  My mother, wife, and I went there tonight not really knowing what to expect.  We walked in and were immediately seated at a booth.  The waiter came over right away.  I had the shrimp carbonara, and my mother the tilapia.  Both were great.  The food was underpriced in my opinion.  Would recommend to anyone looking for good seafood at a surprising cost.

Really cute cafe. Can get a bit busy on weekends so recommend calling ahead to get on the waitlist. We ordered the French toast and the soft scramble. Both were delicious, and the French toast was especially delicious (it was served with orange butter, which was incredible). The staff is great. Coffee drinks there are really expensive ($7 for a latte?). Cocktails are reasonably priced for a brunch place, and it's nice that they serve so many different kinds over brunch.

Yalll...omg..that's all i can say! OMG! 5 STARS! From the customer service to the drinks to the seafood boil!!! So bomb. Visiting from md, i can say this is one of the best seafood spots I've ate at! Me and my bestfriend both got the Combo A with the mr and mrs crab special sauce i forgot the name of the drink but so strong and delicious. Will definitely be coming back when visiting Clearwater! Don't think twice, GO! :)

Best Italian food! Came here for the first time since the expansion and food was just as amazing, if not better! My husband and I had a cozy table in the window. Our server was friendly. We shared a prosciutto and caprese appetizer that tasted so fresh. I had the puttanesca for my entree and my husband had the carbonara. Both were served on pasta cooked to perfection and the pasta to sauce ratio was spot on. We finished our meal with a big piece of tiramisu and it was just the perfect amount of sweetness. We will definitely be back soon!

I am usually very pleased with the excellent customer service and exceedingly well-trained and professional staff at the Edge District Suncoast Credit Union Branch at Central and 10th here in Saint Petersburg, FL.  However, today, despite the fact that the internet indicated that branch is supposed to be open from 9:30am to 6pm, it is still closed and locked.  I called up the customer service department and spoke to a representative and told her that, and she could not provide me with an acceptable or logical explanation.  I asked her to please transfer me to her supervisor because I was not satisfied with her answer, and she pretended she couldn't here me, so I ended up ending the call.  Now why she couldn't just call someone while I was on hold and ask them to update the website as "closed" simply, easily, and instantly, leads me to feel there is really nothing special about Suncoast Credit Union EXCEPT for the excellent customer service and professionalism of the employees at that particular branch.  As a matter of fact, I may just dump this Credit Union completely because the phone rep was so crappy .

One of our favorite spots in Philly.  The best Fish and Chips,  hands down. Charming Irish pub in an old brownstone.  Delicious margaritas. Shout out to Brian K., our professional waiter who really knows how to work the back dining room!

I have a love hate relationship with this place.  They use to have phenomenal sushi. I don't consider myself an expert but I can definitely tell the good from the bad. However they got a new sushi chef and it's not the same. Sometimes the rolls will have A LOT of rice, which stinks because then you get filled up QUICK. Sometimes there will be just the right amount but the rolls fall apart. My favorite roll is the spider roll but I can't order it there anymore because they must not be using the right parts of the crab. Some pieces will taste great but then it becomes FOUL. I've spit it out numerous times. Unfortunate because it's expensive. I hope they get a new sushi chef soon. The take out it good tho.
The Cherry Blossom roll was very good. Wasn't too busy late afternoon Tuesday. In Reno for Hot August Nites.
Amazing food. Best beer and selection in town. You won't believe the food you are getting for the price. Awesome location, awesome atmosphere and fantastic friendly service.

I love this place in the Marigny. I didnt realize they were open for breakfast (sorry, brunch) on Saturday,but when I found out, I headed there with my daughter. We had a great meal and were able to sit outside. I had the lemon ricotta pancakes, and my daughter had a crabmeat benedict. Both were outstanding. The pancakes were like pillows of lemony deliciousnesswith a nice blueberry compote on the side. The crabmeat benedict was amazing, with huge chunks of crabmeat and for a very reasonable price. This is one of those restaurants we in New Orleans don't want to lose. Please patronize them so they can stay open and continue serving delicious and affordable food!!.
A true Tampa Cuban old school quality restaurant w good food, good portions that's always served w a smile.

this RESTAURANT deserves 5 stars, this LOCATION gets a 3 . the food is so great that I hate to complain however I've been a big fan of the amount they give you at the Delmar loop location. I get the bestie combo (two choices of meat and two sides) sounds like a lot of food right? and it is.  I always have enough to eat that night, then take home left overs. not at the Saint Charles location. I guess i will have to continue to drive a little further to get the bang for my buck.

I suppose an out-of-towner would not like coming here, but for whatever reason I end up coming here more often than I'd like to admit.

It is attached to the Facenda-Whitaker bowling alley, and can be entered either from the outside or the actual alley itself. It has changed a lot over the years, as it was an absolute dump when I was younger. It has grown and improved greatly since then, expanding now with an outdoor patio. Sure, that patio gives you a great view of the parking lot, but its a patio all the same.

I am pretty much guaranteed to see somebody I went to high school with here at any time day or night, but its still a decent place. Beers are relatively cheap (go for the pitchers), though you will have to deal with a plastic cup. The food is average bar fare...I've had better wings and I've certainly had worse. Decent snackage but I can't imagine why anyone would order a cheesesteak when Pudge's and Lee's are so close. Stick to the drinking, but don't look for any exotic shots or mixed drinks...its classier than it used to be but not at that level. 

They have more then enough TV's to cover sporting events, with some bigscreens behind the bar. It lends itself well to football Sunday's, and can get pretty crowded at those times. 

Its nothing terribly unique, but its the local of choice (almost by default). Had I not grown up here I would probably hate the place, but I find it endearing. Its probably the smell.

Walked a mile and a half to get to this place from the French quarter. Well worth every step! The service was very friendly, the sweet tea was perfectly refreshing and the food was out of this world. We shared the Superdome and the Bourbon Street. Everything was fresh, good portions and tasty. The mac and cheese under the fried chicken was the best part of the meal. And, always fans of good customer service and personal pride in ones craft, having Chef Jeff come out to chat us up and offer delicious bread pudding was the icing on the cake. Pay no mind to the location. The food and service puts it in my top 10!

I just really, really love sushi. The rolls are colorful and look like works of art. It's also taste great, the only thing that set it apart from many other sushi places is the Yellowtail Cheek.

Cheek, is usually a mystery if you are actually getting cheek or just a "cheek-shaped" nugget from the filet. You can see just by the presentation you are in all actuality getting cheek.

We were the only one in the restaurant and it seems to me that they way to go is to get your order to-go. During our diner 3 to-go orders were served. I would definetly have them again, but I would go the to-go route.

ALERT Ripe off Company 

I pay a monthly fee for this company for services...Had an issue with my heat and everything was all good the technician came and looked at the furnace and told us what the issue was and told me it was under warranty. Great news.. not really he told us that the job is going to be $675...so i asked why so much and he told us that company charges to order a FREE  part under warranty plus labor (that is RIDICULOUS).....so next day called and spoke to a women in office and claims the tech shouldn't have told us this and job was MISPRICED and it should be $750 (WHAT)  but will honor the price of $675. So we figured out a price(better lol i guess) then turns around says we have to full payment before they order the part and do the work and I started laughing and told not gonna happen will give half now and half when job is done... she told me cant happen and full payment is required to do anything....end result we Cancelled everything with this company and got the job done for $250 

BE CAREFUL

I just signed up for a year here, and am loving it so far.  While it's pricier than what I would've gotten through YMCA's financial aid open doors deal, it's far more convenient-- I basically hop on a bus outside of my apartment and 10-15 minutes later I'm there.  The area is really nice, two great food places are nearby (Mugshots and the Belgian Cafe, which I have yet to try out).  The staff is really friendly overall, though I have my reservations about 2 people (then again, I'm quite the Judgy McJudgerson, they're probably nice people).  It's definitely a small gym, with lots of equipment, but I never really feel crowded and the weight lifting equipment is great.  Bikes and treadmills are fine, but I kind of wish they would fit in a few more treadmills (is it just me, or does it seem like there are too many ellipticals?)  Also, it'd be nice if each treadmill had its own tv, but I digress...
I've been to several yoga classes, usually vinyasa and an intro class on Saturdays, and loved all the instructors so far.  I'm somewhat of a newbie to yoga and in most classes, the instructors walk around and help you on your poses-- I find that really helpful.  Locker rooms are fine, and the built-in lock system sure is handy.  I see a variety of people here, not just all students, which is also nice...everyone seems friendly and courteous.

The few caveats:
They rarely run the fans (why? I should probably ask).
Hearing "gym music" (you know, uplifting pop stuff) while cooling down in yoga is kind of a distraction, but I guess it can't really be helped.
No A/C that I can speak of, which does get annoying.  It's not overwhelmingly hot and sticky though (usually), and as long as no one minds seeing my cherry-red dripping tomato face and body after a workout that wouldn't normally leave me in such a state (in an air-conditioned gym), I'm okay with it.

Top Gun Collision Center did a GREAT job repairing my 2007 Mazda Miata.
A truck rear-ended me and put big dents in the bumper and trunk.
Their paint job was a perfect match to the original and you'd never know I'd been in a fender-bender.

Thanks so much to Randi, Loretta and everyone else who helped turn a lousy day into a happy story!

Ok I'm a huge fan of McAlister's. Let's just start there. And after a long time walking a friend and I decided that's what we'd get. Honestly I was super excited. Once I got there after looking over the menu (and seeing the prices being higher than the last time I'd been there (roughly a year)  I decided to get the choose 2 meal. I chose the BLTA which is a blt with avocado, and a spud Mac which comes with turkey, ham, onion, cheese, bacon, and black olives (I 86ed the olives). After getting my bag I checked the food and 1. My bltA was missing the avocado. I mean it's in the name how do you miss it. Then I looked at my spud max, it was missing bacon. I mean I just don't understand how you forget what goes in something, especially when it has a description on the menu. Then when they gave me the bacon for the potato they just gave me two STRIPS of bacon. I mean can you chop it up or something for the potato? . I don't know, either way the food tasted good, I just highly dislike when my food isn't made right especially when I'm really ready to eat.

The customer service here is great!   We went in looking for new bedroom and living room furniture.  We found some items we liked but they were not available for delivery when we needed them.   That was disappointing; however, Nicole was very helpful during our shopping experience.  Ask for her when you go in!

Nice experience! Delicious food and nice staff. The "teriyaki" chicken was my favorite. Not remotely sure why it's called that as it's not like any teriyaki I've ever had nor Asian in flavor whatsoever. Was a nicely seasoned braised chicken.  I was confused if we clear our own plates or not because it was hard to get them cleared. The music is my biggest critique. There was like someone's cell phone playing maybe in the kitchen or something? That's what it sounded like. The place is full of character and color. It's a serious missed opportunity to not have an atmosphere. Some proper speakers and music in there would make it a destination spot for sure

Best BBQ in NOLA!! The place also has a large bar with great cocktails. Would definitely recommend this place to all you BBQ lovers and those who just like BBQ, you'll be very impressed!! YUUUUUUUMMMMMMMMM!!!!!!!!! The Mac & cheese was a great side too! Can't wait to come back to NOLA for round 2!!!

Where does an oyster go for a drink?

An oyster bar!

Acme's the place to go for beer, oysters, lightning fast shucking, and all the abita beers available.

Sitting at the counter is a necessity.  Best views of the heaps of oysters, shuckers and their humor, and whatever game is on TV, unless it's a Saints game, because there's no way that you could stay on a stool with a crazed hoard of Saints fans in a bar.

Just order oysters on the halfshell, an Abita seasonal ale, a side of red beans and you'll be set for your pre-party.

Great Mexican food just off State Street.  They have a great patio that would have been wonderful but we decided to eat inside because it was windy and cold. They do have heaters on the patio so it would be wonderful with out the wind. 

The food was good but nothing over the top amazing. If you are looking for good Mexican food at a good price this is the place.
Food was decent, wife had shrimp fajitas and was happy, I had enchiladas and they were good as well. I can not rate a Mexican restaurant higher than a 3 when you have to pay for chips and salsa.

Excellent atmosphere and better food. Blackened grouper sandwich was perfectly done. Homemade chips were a pleasant surprise, as was the Yuengling. 

Service was also fantastic. Well done.
Pricey, but the best location for drinks on the beach at sunset. During the day, they have a drink cart that goes between the rented chairs on the beach. The perfect amenity :)

This is my first time doing dine-out hot pot.  This is something I usually do at home with my family.  Hot pot with too many people can become very expensive due to the amount of extra items you order.  
I decided to give this place a try with my friend.  We did the single serve shabu (spicy broth) which was a good deal (12.95), it came with a plate of meat of your choice (pork, chicken, beef) and a bowl of vegetables (corn, cabbage, mushroom, some vermicelli).  We also ordered sides of tofu (very smooth), udon noodles, vermicelli.  

The spicy broth:  it was seriously spicy, almost lacked flavor because I couldn't taste anything but spice.  I can tolerate spice, but at least have some flavor other than HOT!!!!!!  There was some beads in the broth where if you unfortunately took a bite of it will immediately ruin your taste buds. My friend and I unfortunately took a bite of it and really was the worst taste ever experienced.   I'm not sure why they're in there, but certainly didn't give the broth anymore flavor than what it was lacking already.  

The sauce bar: there were a huge variety of sauces, but I would recommend the restaurant to get plates with multiple wells because it's an inconvenience to walk back and forth if you want more than 2 types of sauce.

Overall, hot pot is a unique type of dining.

I guess the old "bait and switch" tactics are still alive and well at Mall Chevrolet in Cherry Hill, NJ.  I drove all the way there from Philadelphia after talking with a internet sales rep for 2 days about a USED Ford Explorer they have advertised. I literally called at 7:30pm while in the car driving to the dealership!!!  He responded, "great, come on in".  Lo and behold!  By the time I got there, the car was no where to be found!  And neither was he!!!  Clearly they have no respect for anyone's time. I would never do business with them or recommend their location to anyone. And if shopping for a chevy, you are much better off going to an honest dealership, like  Bergey's Chevrolet (better deals too).

If I wasn't desperate for breakfast and if Einstein hadn't been on my way to an appointment, I probably wouldn't have stopped. It's not because of the service (usually), but because the place is so inconvenient to get into. I'm not sure who designed the drive-thru, but it's a nightmare. It's in an awkward location and it's difficult to navigate.  As for this particular visit, it wasn't the greatest. I spent 10 minutes in the drive-thru and there were only 2 cars in front of me. But because of the awkward layout of the drive-thru, I was kind of stuck. After I ordered a plain bagel, I learned they were out of plain bagels. It wasn't even 10 am. Isn't that a staple??  And then when I got my order, I didn't get napkins and the guy at the window had completely disappeared.  I'll probably be back, but will make sure to go inside.

A SB friend recommended the place and met up with us here last Sunday (and my birthday!) morning.  My eyes lit up upon entering - cases of texas chocolate cake, bear claws, and buttery scones. 

A sweet lady working the front took our names and suggested we wait until we had a table before we ordered - lest we got our foods while still standing. 

I got the kahlua-soaked banana french toast. Of course. I think it's been beat over the head on Yelp about how good it is. Let me join the chorus: it was amazing (underscored). Mouthfuls of liquer-coated challah drowning in saccharine, bombarded with chunks of banana. If the French really made toast like this, their pain perdu would be heart attack central (no mistranslation pun intended). 

The greek frittata was devoured. Accompanying fruit (pineapple, strawberries, blueberries) was fresh. My friend's lobster benedict was bleeding hollandaise (this dish is bookmarked). 

My cappuccino looked like a mini Mt. Everest on arrival. The froth was almost double the height of the cup. It was an honest and delicious pour.

First time there and the atmosphere was nice and cozy. The rice milk they give you is AMAZING. Honestly I could just drink that and be happy, but it's not on the menu to order. The ramen was good, but the broth was a tad salty. The edamame portion is big and also salty, but still good. The karage chicken was delicious, but my husband get it was a bit too mushy for his liking. Overall I'd go back, but I wouldn't run back.

Been to Merchants before and this was definitely a five-star visit. We sat upstairs at a couple different tables with our large group. Started off with several appetizers, the most and far away notable was their crabcake special. Never have I had such moist, fresh, and flavorful crabcakes!

For my entrée I had their small prime rib. Nice cut of meat, cooked to perfection and simply delicious. Loved their horseradish as well. Ordered several shareable sides, but the broccoli and carrots were my favorites.

Full bar, lots of beer selections but no drafts (since it's a historic building they are not allowed to run draft lines). The El Diablo, albeit a little sweet, was a great mixed drink. Zander did a great job serving us!
Service was great. The server read my mind and was very prompt with drink refills. The pancakes were burnt and hard. The moons over hammy was yummy and hot. The hash browns were burnt and greasy.

Not long ago, I was SO OVER the Saucer. Service was perpetually terrible, always out of numerous beers, meh food, smoky, crowded (with tables always "reserved"...weird for a bar), too many bros way too old to be ogling chicks in schoolgirl skirts, pay parking, TERRIBLE bands and always a cover. But the past two or three visits have convinced me to put in back on the drinking rotation.

SMOKE FREE! NO MORE CIGARS! The service is still spotty, but the last time was particularly good, with a knowledgeable and pleasant waitress getting us samples before committing to a pint of something new. NO COVERS ANYMORE! And a few times they had pretty good bands (70 year old soul singer, rockabilly...). The overgrown frattys are still there, but are so much more tolerable when they can't smoke cigars. Makes for good people watching though!

Parking still sucks. Especially when there's an event downtown and the lot behind the bar goes to prepay rather than allowing you to get it validated inside. There isn't a lot of street parking in the area. I'm sure it's still really crowded on Mondays, and for Trivia nights (when we played here we used to have to get there 2 hours before the game to get a table).

Yay improvement!

One of the best birthday dinners I've had. A special and intimate night for sure.

You need a reservation right now, they are not taking walk ins. Free parking right behind their restaurant where it says customer parking only.

We made a reservation for the omakase shogun with the sake pairing. I was honestly SO full from this meal. My husband had to help me finish my food and sake lol. Each dish was amazing and plated beautifully. 

Arte explained each sake that was paired with the dishes. He was fun and energetic throughout our meal. Chef Rexley explained where the fish from the dishes came from as well as explained to us the other non fish dishes. This was our first time having uni and it was so good! There was also another chef/assistant? that prepared some of our dishes and he was great too (sorry didn't catch his name!).

One for the best meals and experiences I've had at a restaurant. Honestly, every bite was delicious. A lot of care was taken in our meal and service. Highly recommend for a memorable evening.

The food was excellent! It was confirmed by our friend who was visiting from Pakistan... she said it was her first meal in the USA that was just like home!

The prices were very reasonable for large portions, unlike most Indian restaurants in the area that charge an extra $3-4 for every dish of rice. The service was exceptional as well. This will definitely be my new go to spot for Indian food!
Over 2 years later we are still loving every visit, and my now 6-year old is always looking fresh with his amazing haircuts.

We ordered a pandemic pizza and it was ready for pickup upon arrival. There was great outdoor seating which is ideal during a pandemic. They had about 10 four-tops with covered umbrellas. We were lucky and no one was eating there so we got to eat completely alone which is great for my covid anxieties. 

They were having a special pizza, the Buffalo pizza, and I used that white sauce to make my own custom pizza with all my favorite toppings. It was actually yummy enough that time to time I think about it and want to go back! But we don't have any super close to our home. So it'll just have to wait. 

The service was good and everyone did seem to wear masks and gloves. Two thumbs up!
Just all around amazing food. Steak lo-mien  is amazing  and so are the dumplings. Will totally come back

Just left Honey Grow and stopped at the condiment counter to get forks and sauces, and noticed one of their employees was on my heels.  At first I thought she was trying to get past me so I stepped aside.  When it became apparent she wasn't, I continued getting my sauces and forks. That's when it hit me. The drink machine is over here. She's trying to make sure I'm not taking a free drink.  Well... IDIOT, I didn't even have a CUP, so there was no need to stand so close to me that I could feel your breath on my back.

Managers of Honey Grow... you have GOT to come up with a better form of security than this. If you are that protective over your soda machine, put it behind the counter. This was intrusive, insulting and annoying. I just spent $40 in your restaurant, but will never spend another penny there. Keep your soda.

When you come back to a place over and over and it always feels like you're family, you know there's something special about it! Frenchy's has been near and dear to my heart for many years. We've done it all here.... birthdays, special occasions, celebrity sightings, Sunday Funday and more, plus their amazing frozen rum runners are life! I was shocked to see you can get them in a bigger size now. Cheers guys! Just make sure you're safe out there! Nice touch with the frozen cups now too! 

The food is always fantastic and fresh! You cannot go wrong with anything on the menu, but here are my tried and true faves in no particular order: she-crab soup, grouper nuggets, grilled octopus, fish tacos, and the crab fries. 

Service is top-notch and consistently outstanding. There's nothing you can't ask for. They do an amazing job with our bigger parties. I swear I wanna be friends with everyone that works here. The best part is that you're facing all the beautiful white sand on Clearwater beach! Frenchy's is bae!

I have actually been here several times and am nearly ALWAYS more than happy with my experience.  Tonight was not one of those nights but I'd really rather not focus too much on it because it was one of maybe 20 times and it just isn't fair to post a review solely based on one slightly bad experience.  The one thing I took  away from the evening is this: Lindys is a burger joint....a damn good one.  It would serve you best to stick to the burgers.  It's what they do best and really do it better than most others in town.  
They have recently moved their location across the street (4th Ave) to a much  larger restaurant that makes dining there much easier and more comfortable.  The burger I've been eating most frequently is called The Cow Tipper   This is an insanely good hamburger that comes with a side of Au Jus!  I can't imagine why more burger places don't do this.  It's really an amazing meal!  My dad usually had the Dirty Sanchez (hee hee) and it is also fantastic!  You can, of course, build your own but I'd recommend goin with one of their signature offerings. These people know what they're doing.  I've also heard they've opened a second spot out on the east side but we haven't made it there yet!  If you haven't been to Lindys....by all means GO!

New to the area and chose this place for lunch. Ordered the gyro and hummus side. Hummus was delicious. The gyro was not what I expected but wasn't bad. Restaurant smelled a little weird to me. Overall, the food was good and at a decent price. Won't be here often but would come back.

1st time customer.  Had a buy 1 get 1 free pizza coupon through entertainment.com via T-Mobile Tuesdays rewards.     Merchant refused to honor the coupon and would not mitigate and provide customer satisfaction.    What is his loss on a buy 1 get 1 pizza considering actual profit?   1st and last visit.    He let me walk out the door dissatisfied and he owns 2 custom pizzas only 1 customer in the place.   Definite terrible customer service.    Never order here....owner was confrontational and extremely unprofessional.

Just joined and I am a fan. Yes, the gym is small but I'm only paying $35 a month and I don't get charged until 9/1/14 and I get access to two other locations. Not bad at all. I completely understand the cancellation policy because I READ the fine print. Pretty simple. Kristen or Kirsten, was very helpful and made the process simple and easy. I go to the gym regularly so I understand the equipment for the most part, so if I needed an explanation she would've helped me out. They DO have parking, just go to the front desk and ask for a sign to put in your car. The only down side is that it's only after 5pm and I go in at 5am, but if you're trying to go to the gym at 2pm on a Saturday when every bar has a special, then don't get upset that there's no parking, thats your fault lol. I haven't experience the gym being packed, but then again I choose to not go during prime workout hours.
Excellent place. Went for a business luncheon. Service was great, food was even better. Will definitely return.

I think I'm in love with Cecil Creek Farm. It's too bad I live in New York instead of New Jersey. I would LOVE to have a place like this in my town, it was adorable and their mission of keeping things local is something I admire. We were on a wine trolley tour and our second stop was at Cecil Creek Farm for a Farm to Table lunch. Our friends have a CSA share there and were familiar so they arranged things. We started with a vegetable barley soup, followed by a tomato and mozzarella Panini with pesto, and finished with apple pie. The staff was so friendly and knowledgeable. The ambiance was exactly what I would have wanted at a farm to table lunch or dinner. They had local goods available for purchase; I could have bought the entire contents of Cecil Creek. During lunch we heard about all of the special events including cooking classes that the farm offers, CSA shares, etc. We grabbed a cup of tea and soaked up the sun outside around an adorable fire pit with Adirondack chairs. I could have lounged there all day. My next trip to visit friends in Philly/Jersey will definitely include Cecil Creek!

Chinese food restaurants are just as common as corner stores in southern New Jersey - and this one I go out of my way to order from - they offer Chinese, Japanese (Sushi), and even some Thai dishes.  I live in Pitman - which is a good ten minute drive - and they deliver for free.

Don't let the location or appearance fool you!  This restaurant sits in an "off the beaten path" location near Dollar General & Green Tree tobacco in a small strip mall.  It appears to have been a pizza parlor prior to being an Oriental restaurant.  The food, service and courtesy is well deserving of a more modern/formal dining room.

I'll save the best for last, THE FOOD!  I love it!  I can't believe the variety of styles that they offer - and the food is absolutely delicious and fresh - their style of cooking most of their dishes is similar but slightly different than many similar restaurants - and I say this because their sauces just taste a bit unique, which is favorable - I can't put my finger on why. 

Their sushi is amongst the best in the area - the rolls don't fall apart when you pick them up, they're the perfect size, the fish is always fresh and the prices are more than reasonable - I love the place!

This is my first experience with apartment and this is company has given me the worst problems with communication and customer service. I have not received the proper customer service since I started with this company. I had an issue with my information with the electric not matching with the electric company and when I called to speak to someone they gave me the run around. Angela Calvanese than suggested that I wait until my move in date to find out if the electric is on or not. I found that to be very unprofessional. Then recommend me to speak to someone else.
Great service by Dwayne who even during the storm when the power was out help me get new petals put on my bike and filled the air.

Some of the yummiest Thai we have had. The only place in the country where I found veg wontons and potstickers which were amazing. We also had their special Thai Green Curry Fried Rice and Thai Rangoon which were really good as well. The service was quick and the place was peaceful and clean too. Absolutely the place to visit for vegetarians.

Love their coffee, but what a continuing disappointment this place has become, as its staff consistenly decides to pack up long before the listedclosing time.  So they shut things down or actually wash the floor around you because it's "not busy."  What a way to run a business.  We really like their coffee and much prefer it over Starbucks, but come on, more than an hour before closing and everything's cleaned.  This has happened so many times, we simply won't go back unless it's early in the day. I wish I had the owner's name to tell him what goes on when he's not around.
I had a really great time at escape my room. Phineas deserves a raise for staying in character with my group lol. I would recommend this place to everyone.

Yes, I'm definitely a fan!
I'm not a beer drinker, and I know they have 65 beers available, but I can't comment on that.
I love food, and I think two meals I've had there are pretty great.
Been twice.  Their hamburger (Bistro Hamburger) was delicious.  
The other meal I've had is the Beef Kabobs.  Absolutely flavorful and would definitely get it again.
My main complaint:  The first time we went, we asked the waitress if there were any specials.  She said no.  When we got home, I went online to peruse the menu again, and was really unhappy to find out that there were several posted on the website.
I was really tempted to call the manager, i was that annoyed that we were told of any food or drink specials that were clearly posted online.
The food was really good, so we went again, however, this woman's laziness almost kept us from not returning.
The gluten free pizza is excellent here.

I will make this like a (grocery) list so I don't forget anything...

Prepared Food: Pizza: 3/5
                             Pork Burrito: 3/5
                             Sushi: 4/5
                             Asian Buffet: 3/5

Beer: Selection: 5/5
           Cost: 5/5
           Freshness: 5/5
           Stupid PA law that only lets you buy two 6-packs: 1/5  :(

Groceries: Ease of finding what you are looking for: 1/5
                    Cost of the products: 3/5
                    Friendliness of the staff: 5/5
                    Variety of products: 5/5

When I ordered a fruit platter: Ease of making the order: 5/5
                                                     Cost: 5/5
                                                     Product Itself: 5/5

Overall I gave Wegman's 3/5 stars for the simple reason is that I hate the layout. I will go there for beer, prepared food and special orders again but not for grocery shopping. For grocery shopping I will stick with a place that has a "grid" layout.

I had a veggie sub on the way to a meeting and it was the best veggie sub I have ever eaten!  It was so good I made my husband go there for lunch the next day and it was just as good as the night before.  We will be coming back here!

This company is also known as "International Granite & Stone".  Please avoid this company.  I am still waiting to get my money back.  Very poor communicators, measuring appointments not honored.  Folks not getting back to me.

I must say that pizza my heart makes delicious pizza. The thing about pizza my pussy is its fresh ingredients. Pizza my perinium only buys the freshest ingredients and toppings. Pizza my anus combines flavor and atmosphere in a really astonishing way. Pizza my labia has a beautiful store front and an inviting aura to it. Pizza my smegma does have steep prices, but it more than makes up for it in cheap, high-quality beer. What strikes me most about pizza my sphincter is its customer service. I always tip the individuals that serve me when I eat at pizza my vulva. You see, the things that separates pizza my scrotum from other pizza joints in isla vista is its ability to make phenomenal pizza, provide thirst-quenching drink and stellar service. Pizza my gooch gets a stellar review from me because pizza my foreskin is a truly memorable pizza joint in a sea of mediocre pizza joints. Thank you, pizza my heart!!

I have been to Blue Willow several times and they have an eclectic and reliable menu.  Each time I have been very pleased with my meal.  Blue Willow has a cozy atmosphere with a charming patio that stays surprisingly cool even on the hottest days.  The service has always been good and the restaurant has a delightful gift shop.

Wow, what a gem. Basically, you can donate things here like books, vintage (or near-vintage) videogames, records...and also to go treasure hunting for these items as well. Every location is slightly different, so be sure to visit often, if that is your thing, like it is mine! Large selection here, also there are boardgames! I also found the rest of the Dune series here to complete my collection, you never know what you will find!

My family of 5 had easter brunch at 930./AMAZING! Where do I start? We were seated right away, staff was SUPER friendly. Buffet food was delicious, they were constantly bringing out fresh serving, the omelet line had a staff member taking people orders in line, it was incredibly efficient. Our tables were cleared right away, drinks came right away. The place was busy too. It's just a well run establishment. I HIGHLY recommend.

I love diners. This one certainly compares to the best diners I've visited. I got a western omelette with grits and toast. Great bang for the buck - that was a borderline obscene amount of grits - but hey, the more the merrier. No complaints there. Props for being a block from our hotel too.

Liar and scammer! That guy dimitri plays so nice but is a liar and fraud!! I do not recommend this place that's all I needed to say for people to be careful! And the good reviews are for the older original owner of this place and I see why he has none of he's so good then why not? Because he's No good!!!!

This is the first time I tried this place and  I was surprisingly surprised. I had a combination dinner pad Thai and coconut soup. The soup was very tasty as I never had coconut soup before. The pad Thai was exactly what I was expecting and it did not disappoint. The restaurant had great Thai decor and music. The staff and service was top notch. For a town with not much selection for food, this was a great change of pace. This may become my go to place in Carp.
Joanna is the best, she does a great job. The woman who runs the shop is great too I've had both of them do my nails and they last a long time.

Great dive bar in an inconspicuous location that serves absolutely delicious "Sandywiches."  I had the "Tailgater" sub which included hot pepperoni, cheese, and roast pork. I added broccoli rabe and it was a pretty great meal and way above expectations. Sandwiches are are served with chips, and a reminder as others have said that this establishment is cash only. Tap beer is your typical bud, coors, yuengling, Stella, and a rotating troegs. If you're looking for craft beer you're in the wrong place. 6 packs are available for purchase to-go.

Let me preface this review by stating that I was terrified at the thought of going to a chiropractor and have someone manipulate my spine.  However, my spinal health took a recent turn for the worse and I was even less enthusiastic about going to an orthopedist and having them tell me that surgery was my only option.

My woes began back in October when I was involved in a hit and run accident while riding my motorcycle.  Although I was lucky to be alive and did not suffer life threatening injuries, I "tweaked" a lot of body parts, including my back.  Things got a little better but I recently spent an entire day pulling up cement forms from a recent home improvement project.  I could feel my back was stiff but I attributed it to a hard days work.  However, when I woke up the next morning, I could not even put on my own socks due to the immense pain in my back.

At the recommendation of a coworker (thanks Richard), I immediately called Dr. Ryan Russo at the Lakeview Regional Chiropractic Clinic in Lakeview.  Even though it was a Friday and he was going out of town that evening, he agreed to see me.  On my first visit, we discussed my issues, he took some x-rays and discussed some treatment options.  He did not adjust me on my first visit, as he needed to see the x-rays first to make a proper diagnosis.  I iced up that weekend as per his instructions and came back on Monday to begin my treatments.

It was difficult for me to relax for my first adjustment, but Dr. Russo told me everything he was going to do, prior to him doing it so that there would be no surprises.  I have been going for approximately three weeks now and have made significant strides towards getting back to my old self.

Dr. Russo is a "younger" chiropractor (30something) and is interested in treating the cause of back problems and not just "chasing pain".  His mission, as qutoed on his website, is "To restore and maintain health through chiropractic care, allowing patients to live their lives to the fullest". He also states on his website that "We're committed to putting your health first by finding the cause of your problem rather than chasing the symptom".

I am a firm believer in him and his clinic, and he practices what he preaches about good health, which is also a big part of good chiropractic health.  I have learned a lot from him about anti-inflammatory supplements and foods that will help improve my spinal health.  He doesn't "push" these supplements on his customers, and actually does not even sell them, so they is no pressure to buy anything.  Simply put, he is honestly interested in improving his patients' health in every way possible.

If you suffer from any type of back pain and live in the Lakeview area, I implore you not to put it off and give Dr. Russo a call. Or, you can check out his website at http://nolachiropractor.com/

Stay healthy!

I went for the very first time on Labor Day! I will definitely be back we started with the goats cheese crab dip it was amazing with the bacon jam. Me and my husband share the captains plate although I have had better oysters it was very good. We enjoyed the atmosphere our server Danielle was awesome she suggested a draft beer that was excellent with our meal. 
If you're ever in Dunedin this is a great place to visit and have good food.

We stayed here for a beach wedding. The location on the water is fantastic and the staff was very friendly and accomodating. Rooms are good size for what you pay - ours had two bedrooms, two bathrooms, a kitchen and a little living room space. Our view of the Gulf was fantastic. Our room smelt a little fishy. The housekeepers couldn't seem to get rid of the smell either and the floors were a little sticky. I really wish this place had a restaurant on site and not just a café. The café closed at weird times and we kept having to walk to the gas station. It would have been nice to be able to stay somewhere not leaving every time for a meal. The pool is a bit outdated and could use some work. The little hut bar is a cool feature but the bartender was not friendly and it just seemed a bit dirty to me. Outside of the building could use a little TLC but everything is this area is pretty old and warn down. Probably wouldn't stay here again but A+ for the staff!

If you've ever walked into heaven, then you're either on drugs or dead. But...this place is AWESOME! The air in this place must be supplemented with nitrous because the whole place is warm and fuzzy and it just makes you smile. 

Kick-ass spa, no 2 ways about it!

Excellent cheesesteak. We came on a Saturday afternoon and the line wasn't crazy. Our food came out quickly and we were able to get a high top table. The roll was fresh, steak was perfectly cooked, and you could actually taste the whiz (I hate when you get a cheesesteak, but the cheese is barely there or is too thin/runny). Highly recommend you get it with the peppers, as well. One of my favorite spots for a steak, and I'll definitely be back.
I took my boyfriend here this morning an hour after we made an appointment,and we were in and out in less than an hour! Jennifer did an amazing job!

Came to Punch Line Philly in the beginning of July for a meet and greet / drag show. When we arrived we got our bracelets and were told to sit at the bar until a crowd or line formed. Punch Line has a two drink minimum. It's required once you are in the showroom. -- Although I knew about the minimum, I didn't realize it was only in the showroom. So I ordered a beer out by the bar thinking it would contribute to that. My fault. We also decided to order an app because we were starving. We ordered the margherita pizza. It was pretty good! The crust was so flakey making a mess everywhere though.

Once it was time to form for the meet and greet, they had a line literally wrapping around the outside of the building. Things went pretty fast which was nice. The staff was definitely efficient in getting everyone in and out. When entering the showroom someone will guide you to your seats. Our table was directly, front row and center of the stage. What luck!

Once I was informed that our outdoor drink didn't contribute we were talked into ordering the larger margarita because it would count as two drinks and we would be hitting our minimum. It was $48 for two margaritas (ridiculous) -- not to mention it tasted like juice. Made our stomachs hurt quite a bit after too. 

Three stars for the staff / out door bartender / pizza. I definitely would come back for another show, but Punch Line is just your typical comedy club. Nothing out of this world.

Inattentive service and crappy food.  My son was served a mostly uncooked burger, when I brought it to the attention of our server his response was "what do you want want me to do, I can't do anything with this" gesturing to the half eaten burger. At least we didn't have to pay for it. Manager didn't come out to apologize or anything. Fruit cup was old fruit. This is my second time coming here and it's going to be my last. Very disappointed.

Been here many many times to not award 5 stars. My order is always correct, my mobile orders are always ready within a couple minutes, and I've enjoyed the offers and deals through the app recently. Plus the staff is very nice and quick. No complaints!

Worst drunken noodles I have ever had. It was also delivered 3 hours past placing the order and when we tried to cancel after 2 hours they said they couldn't cancel it because they already made it. The food came an hour after that, cold and bland.
I love Cinderella! The place is always clean, and the staff if friendly and kind. my nails always look wonderful and last a while. My go-to!

Dustin is THE BEST. I have used several pool cleaners and Preservation Pros is the most competent, reliable, knowledgeable, reasonably priced and trustworthy company in Tucson. After a bad experience with another company, I called Dustin. He came out right away to fix the problem the other guys couldn't and I have been with him ever since. He has fixed issues that I otherwise would have had to refer to the manufacturer which would have cost me a lot more. He also hooked me up with someone who fixed my solar panel. It's a big relief knowing Preservation Pros is caring for my pool so I can just enjoy it!  Thank you Dustin.
Huge fan. Have never had a bad meal here. Blackened redfish is my go to here and the oysters are superb, cold, salty and fresh. Wife is also a big fan.

Ordered a pie before a trip to the airport and was pleasantly surprised by:

+food was ready in 10 minutes
+fresh ingredients, great tomato sauce and cheese on the south brooklyn pie
+abundance of basil on each slice
+reasonable price for a medium pie ($16 with quality ingredients)
+ thin yet chewy crust 

super excited to have found this place... foresee a lot of visits here in the future!!

What a hidden gem!! 
So delicious! The staff was all super friendly and helpful. 

Choosing what to get was hard, but a previous review lead me to go with the shrimp mofongos

They did not disappoint! 
Savory and flavorful cooked with love. 
The empanadas were also delicious filled with yummy goodness.
The seafood selection are good. Wish the clams could be bigger for a clam lover guy like me.
Visited several times and always a nice experience. The staff is prompt and the food is outstanding!

Paid for ceiling tiles to be rehung and for some wall ceramic tiles to be placed.   You can see from the pictures that the work was not well done.  He also broke a large lighting fixture.  He did respond quickly,  and reduce the price since he broke the lighting fixture.   However,  I now need to pay double (to remove his work and redo it with someone else).
I had dinner here last night and had the grouper sandwich which was really fresh and really good. The atmosphere is fun and Carlton is the best bartender ever!

This is awesome spot to eat, drink and bowl!! We had the loaded tater tots and flatbread pepperoni pizza along with a pitcher of Abita Amber. The food was delicious and the atmosphere was excellent. They played good music and the service was friendly and quick! I would highly recommend going here to bowl. Keep in mind though it's a little pricy; it cost us roughly 60.00 an hour to bowl.

The brisket is out of this world: juicy, tender, full of hickory smoked taste, and the Jack's Creek BBQ sauce completes this signature dish of Tennessee. But wait, please also try the whole hog pull pork. It is even better. Side dish of deep fried hush puppies, and baked beans, perfect compliment to the meat. Ambience and friendly bartender make it a perfect 5 star! 200 lbs plus whole hog smoked for 24 hours to show for! Excellent!

This is a TRUE "dog run". I've never been to a dog park with so much square feet of grass for dogs to really sprint around! My 25lb terrier had the time of her life in the small dog park section, running around and socializing with dogs her size.

I really love that the "small" dog park section had enough space for the dogs to really run around, as opposed to some that are usually a smaller, cramped area next to a larger park.

The only downside: rangers close the park as soon as it gets dark.

Loved, loved, loved the sandwiches!  The bread is soooo good!  Thank goodness Dierberg's carries them!  Ambience was kinda hip & cool.  They have a lot of tasty treats!  The rooibos hot tea could have been better.  But, hey they don't make it themselves.  It comes out of a box.  Staff was very friendly.

I like this place. It's like a modern food court with a variety of food options, lots of space. Its easy to find . the chicken and waffle place is A+ Try the shrimp.



Cons:
It's downtown so parking is not free and can be hard to find.

This place has got it going on!  Yes it's in a gas station across the aisle from a convenience store but these guys are making a phenomenal food! 

The garlic sauce on the chicken is amazing and the sauce for the gyro is even better, with fresh onions sprinkled on  top 

Both meats are outstanding but I prefer the gyro meat, its nicely spiced and expertly cooked.  Portions are big enough I get second lunch out of it 

And although I've only gotten to go there are a few tables you could seat at and eat, places is very clean

If you have a Can Am I would recommend taking it to Mandeville than this place because the costs are crazy to say they're not necessarily the best at fixing it. I bought my Can Am from a personal seller and when the bike started giving me problems I bought it to Power Sports. Long story short I paid $2,230 just for them to tell me they needed more money to find what the problem is. I chose to just pick up the bike and take it to Mandeville who were able to fix it. Thanks for charging me $2.3k just to tell me my bike was broke I guess. The staff were friendly at least but shoot I'd be friendly too if I got paid 2.3 thousand to tell someone something they already knew.

Really clean place. I was not expecting much but the wonderful professional staff from front desk.. Housekeeping who held the elevator and offered to help me out with my luggage were incredibly nice!!

I've been a customer here for years and rented trucks numerous times, this is the best location in New Orleans to rent a truck from!  I don't know what else you could ask for in a truck rental service, they always have been helpful and especially generous and friendly in the return process. Here's how it works, you reserve your truck then arrive to pick it up (always get the insurance coverage), put a small reserve on your card and drive away with the truck.  When you return it be on time and it'll only take 2 minutes while they check you in with their mobile app on their cell phones, receipt goes to your email.  I wouldn't think of another place when I need a truck, it's simple.
Great Place with Fantastic Food. The Crab Cakes and The Cornet Burger is Absolutely Phenomenal.  Just can't imagine The Po'boys with Shirmp and served eith friend potato chips.

I am elated that I have found this salon. I have been natural for three years. During this journey, I have been through countless products, countless youtube videos and for the last year or so have been using Marley braids as a way to avoid my natural hair. I guess that I have 4c hair, and not that I don't love it but I just grew frusturated. I have been to other salons that have been able to get my hair straight but the process was disastrous and the perceived benefits did not outweigh the risks. You see everyone is going natural now so people claim that they can do natural hair. But trust me, this isn't the case. If you are interested in healthy natural hair that won't be ruined by heat heavy  stylists, I encourage you to call and book an appointment with the owner, Anika. Check Ryan Foster out on youtube as well.

When I lived in Philly, this was a goto place for some of the folks in our neighborhood.  So when I needed a quick place to go, I figured it was worth a shot.

If I could split this into service and food, service gets a 4 and food gets a 2.  There's not a problem charging 40 bucks for a 8oz filet but it should be damn near perfect.  My first bite was over done and the cut didn't strike me as top prime.  This place, like a lot of it's cohorts, seems way over priced for the quality.  Maybe I'm a hole in the wall type of guy but these steak houses have seriously jumped the shark.
Barbeque shrimp was fantastic.  Anitpasto salad was not bad.  Dessert was okay.  Good times, good food.

The Artessa is a great place to live in Franklin, perfectly located for the shops/mall but also a peaceful, quiet location. We spent 7 months here and loved using the facilities, including a spin room, large outdoor pool (very kid friendly) and spacious gym. The staff are all really friendly and helpful, always on hand to assist. Our apartment was a ground floor 3 bed, and we had no issues. It was spacious, bright and well finished. Move in and move out was a breeze - we'd recommend The Artessa to anyone looking to rent in Franklin.

Drinks = 9.5 Strong, well balanced, and creative. My favorite trip momento is the little zombie pick that came in my drink.
Service = 9 Attentive wait staff, gave great recommendations, super friendly
Decor = 7 This is purely our prefence, but we love the dives with the campy decor the best. This one was a little too bougie for our liking.
Super delicious arepas, and friendly service, will try again! I personally tried the reina pepeada and loved it, excited to try the others!

Just ordered, pickup, at our local pizza place! I love Papa Johns . I just moved from a city that didn't have a Papa Johns so when I saw this I had to order, not one but two extra large pizzas. My favorite is the garden veggie and the tomato & spinach. But then I noticed they have these sandwiches called Papadias! Have you seen those sandwiches?? I haven't tried one yet, almost ordered a couple those too!!!! Check them out online at papajohns.com. The smell of these pizzas makes me drool!!! Did I just say that!!!!!! lol

Is there anything sadder than ordering $50 worth of food and picking-up the bag and it weighs like six ounces?  That does not happen here. Nice portions  of super fresh, well prepared product that's healthy to boot.
It's ok Chinese food. Cheap and fast delivery. Wish fried rice was an option with entrees instead of plain white rice.

I've realized that people always love or hate hotels.  For the most part, I loved the hotel.  I booked 2 rooms for 2 couples on Priceline, which surprised me by getting a 4 star downtown for $100.  I wanted to stay in the French Quarter but I'm glad we stayed a little out of the craziness.
The hotel is beautiful, so I felt like a high roller.

We were put on a smoking floor at first, but they changed it quickly.
The bed was cozy although the pillowtop was falling off and no one adjusted it. The water pressure was low, which could have been better.

But I loved having a gym, even with confusing machines, that I used twice during my trip.  It's open 24 hours with your key.  And it has a water cooler, which was really helpful.  My beau lounged in the pool which is more loungey than good for doing laps.

I was pretty happy with the choice, the location, and the hotel in general.

This restaurant is offering outdoor seating during COVID. Although the weather is changing, and the days are getting cooler, we decided to sit outside for lunch and I am glad we did. I normally go to Chinatown for Pho but wanted to support a local West Philly business. The vegetarian Pho was delicious and the service was great. Our waiter was attentive and explained the differences in the broth options as I am a vegetarian. There is a button on the table that allows you to inform the waiter when you are ready to order, pay, have a question, etc. I think this is helpful as you don't have to question when someone will be out to assist you. I also highly recommend the summer rolls and smoothies. I tried the pina colada smoothie and it made my commute home more enjoyable. I'm looking forward to supporting this establishment again in the near future.

Awesome place to watch an Eagles game or enjoy a bite to eat with a group of friends. The Tradesman's somehow makes classic barbecue feel upscale and refined in a subtle way. 

The atmosphere is boisterous and fun, and the food is even better. We had the cheese plate to start. It featured 3 delicious cheeses, sour cherry jam, local honey, apples, crostinis, and pickled red onion. The pairings were delicious. 

We also ordered the ribs, pulled pork, Mac and cheese, and potato salad. The highlights were definitely the ribs and the Mac and cheese. The ribs were perfectly tender and fall-of-the-bone. I appreciate that they provide a basket of different sauces to put on the meat. The combination of the sweet sauce and the Carolina vinegar was killer on the ribs. The Mac and cheese is perfectly creamy. 

They have a pretty extensive draft list, with lots of happy hour specials. This is a great edition to the Philly food scene!
ridiculously understaffed. 3 people working on Christmas Eve. I have waited for 2 hours and still no food yet.

Bella's has been a longstanding favorite place for family get togethers, lunch with friends and drinks with co-workers. The food does not disappoint, the service always seems attentive and the atmosphere is casual enough to not have to dress up but classy enough to break out that cocktail attire whenever you are in the mood.

The pizza seems to be a crowd pleaser and the pasta is definitely a favorite that makes you realize how delicious fresh pasta can be. Salads are fresh, the food is seasoned - but not in a heavy handed manner - and drinks are promptly delivered.

What more could you need?

The only drawback may be the parking lot which seems to fill up fast and can be a bit of a nightmare to try to navigate because it is such a tight space. If there is valet service that certainly makes a difference because trying to park anywhere in that neighborhood is never easy.

This restaurant has roots in Tampa that date back decades. Not an easy accomplishment these days but certainly a testament to what Bella's does, from the way it makes guests feel appreciated to the way it takes its food to heart and is happy to share the love with its diners.

My first visit to Dat dog was the location on magazine St and the food was amazing but this location, the service was pretty bad. When I came in no one greeted us, my friend and I eventually just sat down ourselves. No one came  to the table so we got up and went to the front register to try and order that way but yet again no one took our order or even  tried to tell us where to sit or what to do because clearly we were confused. We just walked out. I'm sure  the food is good at all locations but the service was horrible and I had to pay to park so a complete waste of time !!

Nice location at the end of the pier and very friendly waitstaff. We got oysters, crab salad, and tacos - the food was just ok. Everyone else seemed to be getting the crab special, so I would get that next time.

The Welly really makes me miss living in Broad Ripple. A little drink, some live bluegrass, and a group of good friends - ah, those were the days. I love how it's tucked away in a corner like a dirty little secret hidden in the heart of the village. Right below the Corner Wine Bar, unmarked like a speakeasy, the Wellington appeals to a pretty casual, mature crowd. Just follow the rabbit hole...

Before I was married, my crew would go here for the comfortable atmosphere. This is not your typical Broad Ripple bar. If you want to avoid the bar hoppers and club crawlers, then you're in the right place. On the weekends, be prepared for a crowded room. The downstairs is VERY small, and only holds a few tables. Get a table early and plan on staying here all night.

Oh - they don't smoke in here anymore. Just FYI.

i would not recommend anything about this business. I cannot believe this place is still in business. Minutes after I left the business after picking up my car, i noticed a pocket knife missing. I always keep it in the change compartment and saw it there when I dropped off my car (i specifically checked). I asked if i needed to remove my valuables prior and was assured that only the manager empties valuables. When I called to report my knife not returned in my box of belongings, i was told that there is no way it was in the car. I am not accustomed to being called a liar but i was not up for the fight so i let it go. Until the next day when my carpets were dry and i was putting my mats back in place i noticed one mat missing. I called again and they couldn't find it. They sent a picture of a mat by text message. Since i could not tell easily, i had to drive out of my way to find it was the wrong size and color although it was from a Honda. it seems as if this is standard practice and they have a surplus of unclaimed mats! I was flabbergasted at this point. I was basically called a liar when i called to report my pocket knife missing and now they can't find my mat. i was promised that they would order a new one which is not possible since these are carpet colored and come with the car, he offered to get a new set of mats from the dealer and replace all of them. I thought it was too much but he assured me it wasn't a big deal since they do alot of business with the dealerships. a week later, i recieve a text that they have my mat. i again drive out of my way and could not believe that there was no new set of mats as promised. They did find the same color and size mat as the missing one however this one had cigarette burns (not only am i not a smoker, but no one has ever smoked in my car so this was obviously NOT my mat). He took the mat over to one of the guys who did something and the burn was not so obvious (i can't be sure but it looks like the cigarette burn was cut out). he asked me if i was pleased. of course i wasn't but after numerous phone calls and trips out of my way, i was so fed up i wanted to be done with them. he offered me a detail on the house but i said i couldn't take the chance that anything else would be missing from my car. no remorse for all my trouble and no apology. he basically shrugged when i said no thank you.  BTW - the pocket knife miraculously showed up too. I can only assume that the "manager" who empties valuables from the car missed this compartment, one of the detailers found my knife and assumed he was in the clear. What really annoys me is that they would not even consider that i was telling the truth without ever asking their employees if they "found" a knife. I gave them a way out but they chose not to take it.

Long story short...don't use this business...The owner either doesn't care or doesn't know what a bunch of idiots and thieves he has employed. they did a good job on my car but the aggravation was not worth it.
Maybe the owner should not have his "manager" handle customer satisfaction.

This is the best little hole in the wall place in Metairie. I have not found one thing the menu that wasn't good.  

I strongly recommend stopping and getting a banh mi. 

The attached pic is the "Steak and Egg" Banh Mi and a side of Bang Bang Shrimp, my favorite.

I'm not usually a Yelp review guy but wow, this place is incredible. The Jasmin rice is so soft and airy that it could attract you there on its own. The samosas, the paneer shahi korma -- even the variety of little sauces that came with the meal were delicious. We'll definitely be coming back.

Great place for mini golf! The course is very well kept with clever holes. The side scavenger hunt keeps you entertained while you wait on other guests (which wasn't long). Very friendly staff. Don't forget to feed the gators before you leave! Highly recommend.
Great brunch ,love the new space,clean,and open,will be back for dinner sometime soon.
Clean / Friendly  employees great food & service gas price is cheap  plus always open 24 hrs  ......

Really great place, left my nails beautiful. So glad they came out amazing because I needed them for this weekend. The wait wasn't that long and the price was great. It all depends on you whether it becomes expensive or not. They do your nails to your preference for not that much extra charge. Wasn't very busy. Only problem was that they only had 2 employees so after I got there, others wanted to get pedicures but they couldn't because both employees were busy. Definitely coming here next time for my Nails!

If you require tasks done efficiently or to see a MD, this is NOT the office for you. Unreliable means of communication (i.e. Fax), untimely completion of tasks, after 4 years I have never been seen by or spoken to an MD.

I'm Puerto Rican. I know arroz con pollo. Alma de Cuba was an Americanized version of it. My husband and I came for Restaurant Week and although the atmosphere was beautiful, the food was simply average at best. Cuba Libre offers tastier food.

Yay! For La Parilla! Last night in Nashville visiting from California and gave this place a shot ... it was good - and that's coming from a SoCal girl that's been spoiled with great Mexican food all her life.
Chips and salsa good, ask for the hotter salsa and it's perfect. Best was the grilled chicken tacos authintica. So happy we found this place cuz we're making an offer on a new home here this week! :D
Just never answers their phone. good luck finding your package...

I mean, it's a Starbucks, not much to say. Service was good, real fast actually. I come here sometimes since it's up the street from work. But if you like Starbucks then I think you'll like this location. Only downfall is no drive-thru & you can tell this one has been around awhile.

Amazingly cute place! Just the vibes walking in are awesome, the energy is chill and inviting!! I had a Carmel Iced chai tea latte & had order of biscuits and gravy. Let me start by saying babbbyyyy the food was more than on point it was   the latte was the best I've had it left Starbucks latte in the dust . They have an extra room that has more seating and is quite if your needing a workspace. I definitely will be back love this spot
The rooms are way spacious in the back building and either they are new or updated. The pool is painted blue and looks very clean. Would be a great budget hotel for families. Very clean.

Believe the hype! Their pancakes will melt in your mouth, stuff you and leave you completely satisfied. There's something on the menu for everyone but be sure to try their house made syrup it's a hidden gem. The wait time can get long but don't let it scare you off, no one would be waiting if it weren't worth it.

We had an event for about 120 people, and they knocked it out of the park.  We were able to design a custom menu for the evening with appetizers and main courses that every single person said was one of the best, if not best meals they'd had at a large event.  Chicken skewers, toasted ravioli, fried artichokes to start, and mains of pasta, perfectly prepared beef tenderloin and philly cheese steaks. I highly recommend hosting your next private party or reception there.

Delicious!! I had the superfoods bowl, which was really yummy. Kids had the chocolate chip pancake which they both loved, my daughter almost ate the entire thing. They were large! Service was good, polite, and moved at a good pace! Ambience was good, normal diner feel but very clean. I'd definitely go back to try more things on the menu. Definitely will head back here next time we're in town.

The family had an afternoon dinner at Chuy's in Nashville.  The outdoor patio seating was just what we needed after a long COVID hibernation exile.  Olivia was one of the best servers in the business! 
Chuy-Changa with medium spice was excellent. Beef fajita, beef fajita burrito, all very good. The tres leches desert was soooooo good, we ate it all! recommend this place.

We had a very large party of 24 last weekend. We had made part of the reservation online thru Open Table and the other over the phone. Open Table mistakenly cancelled our reservation but Jamie at S&S quickly called/emailed to assure us it was only a glitch and that they were still expecting us. Jamie was very accomodating and pleasant when we arrived. They sat us all together in the back room of the restaurant; perfect for our large group of volleyball players and parents. Hunter (server) was on the ball and went above and beyond with our large group. The food was amazing (I highly recommend the crawfish mac-n-cheese paired with a Hurricane) and the prices were affordable. Overall it was some of the best service and food we experienced while in NOLA. The ONLY thing that would have made the night even better was if Channing himself would have been on site. :-)  If you are on Bourbon Street - check it out!

As it's been said before, this is an all-around great restaurant. It's trendy and fun and lively with great food. It definitely draws a younger, college-age crowd but good for families as well. It's always crowded and full of people sipping margaritas happily waiting for a table. I've been here many times and always leave happy. Their margaritas are probably the tastiest in the city but still pack a punch without making you comatose (I'm lookin at you, Superior Grill!). Actually, their whole drink menu is delicious and fun with items like fish bowls and pina coladas. 

The food is good too. The conch fritter appetizers are crispy and fresh. The queso is out of this world. The nachos are AMAZING. Salads have nice flavor combos. And their tacos. All their tacos are superb and my favorite in the city. My advice would be to come on Taco Tuesday to try as many as possible for a good price (but be prepared for a wait!). All their sides are great as well (plantains, grits, sweet potato fries).

Always happy to return!
Austin was extremely personable and attentive. Adhered to both the expected and unexpected needs of the guests, a great asset to the Baja Sharkeez Team!
Great experience!  Family of four came in and had plenty of food. Service was fast!  Terry was excellent.  We really enjoyed our meal.  We will be back!
The Cauliflower pizza was ok.  Expensive for what it is and the size.  This place is kind of depressing and hot inside.  Very lackluster.
Drove out to this establishment because it says they're open. ..its 4pm and doors locked.  Two people sitting on table outside said they closed and will reopen around 4 30....sorry..not coming back

In the span of a 15 minute train ride, PATCO made me vow to start saying my prayers again every night, and possibly even start hitting Sunday mass again. Let me explain. 

Last Friday evening around 5:30, I boarded a westbound train with two other people. The train car was surprisingly empty, but I made a mad dash for the only seat that had a sports page sitting on it. Just as I started to get into the Flyers' injury updates, the lights went out. This seemed odd, but the train was still moving so I didn't think much of it. 

We went underground in Camden, and the darkness in the tunnels was quite spooky. As we approached the first underground station, the train slowed, but did not stop. Same with the second. So the lights were out, we weren't making stops and no announcements were being made. As we made our way out of the tunnel and onto the Ben Franklin Bridge, I text-messaged my sister about the situation and said that I was a little freaked. 

As we went back underground in Philly, I thought we would surely stop at 8th and Market, where I was supposed to get off the train. Again, the train slowed but did not stop. At this point, it is safe to say-- I WAS LOSING MY SHIT!!! Worst-case scenarios featuring gunmen and hostage situations filled my head. 

I abandoned the sports section and made my way closer to the other passengers. A lovely woman by the name of Susan comforted me when I expressed my concern for our safety. For that, I am eternally grateful. 

When the train started slowing to what appeared to be a stop as we got to the 12th/13th & Locust station, I stood up and announced that I was going to pry the doors open with my bare hands if I had to. Which is exactly what I tried to do-- only, the doors were locked. I felt like I was in a horror movie when suddenly, the lights went on and we could see the conductor walking towards us from the car in front of us, a confused look on his face. He opened the door and said, "this train is out of service!" To which all three of us replied (i.e., screamed) something along the lines of "well then why were we let on to begin with?!" peppered with many expletives (mostly mine). 

I shakily made my way above ground, grateful to be alive, grateful for the kindness of strangers and grateful that some taxi drivers don't mind driving drunk girls home to Jersey at the end of the night when they decide to pass on the train.

The service tech was nice.  He came to see why the gas fireplace on my recently purchased home wasn't going on. It was a simple adjustment.   But the home hadn't been cleaned when I bought it.  He had already charged the service call so I let him clean the fireplace.  $140. TOTAL.   I feel that was a heavy charge for Windex and a cloth.   I cannot afford this business.  Quote to add a blower to the fireplace....$500.   Nope..

Despite being the second biggest Walgreen's I've ever been too, this must be the worst Walgreen's ever. I don't know if it was because we were the only three customers there, or if it were the employees who seemed paranoid to have three Asian men walking around looking for toothpaste at night, or if it were stragglers outside in their cars doing God knows what, there was just something about this place that was off.

This may be a long review so grab a glass of wine and read on! I had recently moved back from South Tampa to Carrollwood and I heard about this place from an individual at my health club on Harbour Island. Needless to say I was skeptical. I had very low expectations about a wine bar in Carrollwood.

Well the joke is on me. This place not only exceeded my expectations but blew me away in every aspect! From the moment I walked in I felt like I was a valued customer. Pedro and Chelsea were working and they not only had smiles on their faces entire evening but wanted to genuinely get to know me.
