They had the pour your own glass of wine via the wine dispenser however, due you technical issues it wasn't working that evening. I wasn't mad it's something they can't control however Pedro felt so bad he not only gave me a free glass of wine which by the way was delicious but also gave me 20% off a bottle. Totally unnecessary but very much appreciated and left me feeling valued as a customer. 

I have already told several people about this place and can't wait to visit again!
4 9-10 yr old girls agree that this is the best place for ice cream. Dora helped us try so many favors before ordering our 2 scoops. Great place! Can't wait to come back.

don't come here if you're expecting fresh fruit, what you paid for, or good service. employees are not only rude, they charge you for all the extras you ask for and don't put them on. ended up paying 16$ for a bowl that was worth 5$ max. portions are terrible and they don't give you the extras you ask/pay for. not to mention the pineapple is brown, strawberries are mushy, and dragon fruit is melty (and flavorless). so if you want fresh fruit go to the store and get it yourself, because this place isnt what it advertises.

On January 24th, I went to the web site for making a reservation for March 21, 2018. When I got the emailed confirmation, I realized the date of the reservation was wrong. It showed March 4th, 2018. I immediately call the Hotel. They said there was nothing they could do for me. I called the Radisson Corporation, who said each Radisson was independently owned. They tried to do a 3-way call, and the GM Patel said he would do nothing. I called my credit card, Capitol One, who tried a 3-way call. All we got was a voice mail of Mr. Patel. I left a message explaining, the date of the 4th was incorrect, that I would be happy to pay the full rate on the correct date of the 21st, and to please call me. He never call and Capitol One CC said there wasn't any charges at this time. March 4th, 2018 a CC hold of a charge of $81.22 showed up on my Capitol One CC. I immediately did the same process again: Maria, The Radisson front desk clerk said there was nothing they could do for me, but would try to get Mr. Patel on the phone. again, all I got was his voice mail. I called Capitol One, who again tried a 3-way phone call, and all we got was a voice mail. I again explained the charge was for the wrong date and that I would be happy to pay the full rate of on the correct date of the 21st, and to please call me. Capitol One CC said it was only a hold at this time. On March 8, 2018, I found an actual charge on my Capitol One CC. I called the Capitol One CC to dispute the charge. They tried a 3-way call to the GM Patel, who said he would do nothing. He acknowledge, I called several times,that he could do something, that this was a my mistake, that he would do nothing about it. So, I filed a BBB report, Fraud Reports with Capitol One, and low arks on Yelp, Twitter, Face Book, and Trip Advisor.
Excellent meal, very professional service. Atmosphere is extremely  cozy considering the tight seating.  Low lighting.  Very enjoyable experience overall.

Went to this nice restaurant with my family.  Young children attended.  The wait staff could not have been more helpful in their service to us.  The food arrive promptly and it was delicious.  I hope to go there again.

We stopped by yesterday as part of a food tour. The food was so amazing that we had to go back later for more food. Their chicken tastes so good. The different syrups that they had paired with the chicken is delicious. We had the beast which is this amazing creation of chicken. Bacon dipped in their batter and fried. We also had the cheese curds and nugs. I don't think you can go wrong with any of the food you order here. I definitely recommend swinging in and getting some amazing food.

Havana, the bar, is 5 stars; Havana, the restaurant, is 3. There's no better place in New Hope to grab a drink, whether it's the 4 in the afternoon or midnight. Music is always playing (sometimes a live band!) and the ambience is chill but lively. There's ample outdoor 
seating and room at the bar (even during COVID-19). The menu has a good beer list as well as cocktails. Havana is easily my go-to in town to chill with friends over drinks.

The food is just average, however. I wouldn't say there's much authenticity at all to the so-called Cuban food on the menu. Every dish I've tried is pretty bland, could definitely use some more seasoning (the rice and beans is literally just that, plain rice and plain beans). The food is also overpriced for what it is ($15 for black beans and tortilla chips...). There's very little in regard to dietary considerations, as almost every item has meat in it and they don't note gluten-free items. The silver lining is that a side of fries is always safe bet and the least expensive item on the menu.

Tasty salad! Loved that they asked how much dressing--I don't like a ton, so a 'light' option was great. It was a little pricey, but no surprises there. Head's up--there's no place to sit at this location, it's all grab-and-go.

I found them through Costco's Auto purchasing program. Overall the purchase part was good. Our salesman was very polite. professional, and eager to please. The car was exactly what we wanted in all areas. 

The problem was with the financing dept. Initially we purchased the extended warranty program that they offered. However after a week we elected to drop the warranty. We contacted the dealership and attempted to cancel our original warranty. We could NOT get the finance person (Ryan Erdle) to return phone calls or answer emails. I had to go to the dealership to find another finance person to make the cancellation. All good now, right? Wrong.

This all took place in August of 2015. I had to contact Honda USA to intervene on my behalf in order to get the Ryan Erdle to cancel the warranty. This alone took over one month of Honda USA calling the dealership to do the right thing. 

There was always an excuse. But finally It was submitted, and hopefully in 3-4 weeks something positive will happen. It is now December 2015. 4 months later.

My recommendation is if you use Palm Harbor Honda do not use Ryan Erdle as your finance person.

I'm so confused why it says that this store is closed.  I love it and was just there!?!?  So, maybe I have the name wrong or they changed names?  I'll have to ask next time I am there....

I love this store and it has some great finds.

This is for all Red Lobsters, not just the one on Irvington, this just happens to be the last one I ate at. Anywho...Dont waste your money honey! I ordered the lobster dish I saw on their commercial & what I got was one that was 10 times smaller. My son ordered the petite lobster tail & for more than half the price of my dish, his lobster tail was bigger, yes BIGGER than mine!!

Had a hard time figuring out where to get pizza from and decided to order from here.....This place is Awesome! I am a huge pizza fan and I recommend this place if you are a pizza lover! A little pricey but worth it!

We got Ice cream flight with 5 flavors: cardamon rose, I hate chocolate, kettle corn, cinnamon bourbon and cherry vanilla. The ice cream taste very fresh and flavor wise, the kettle corn was the clear winner among my group of friends. It tasted like caramel.

This is a wonderful place to tan.  Several important things you should know about European Sun: 

1.  It is CLEAN, CLEAN, CLEAN
2.  The staff is amazingly warm and welcoming
3. The beds are properly cared for; they regularly (read: often) replace the bulbs to ensure maximum efficacy of the beds. 

I wanted to write a review for European Sun because it is not often that you find such a lovely place to tan.  It is by far one of the cleanest tanning places I've ever been to.  I have watched the staff clean the beds and they put some serious energy into ensuring the beds and the rooms are properly cleaned.  Also, it is truly a pleasure to visit European Sun.  Every person that works here is kind and friendly and acts genuinely happy to have you there.  When you walk in you always get a friendly "Hello" and I've never left without someone telling me "Thank you" and/or "Have a nice day."  It is wonderful to visit a business that seems genuinely happy to have you as a customer.  I believe the staff is so friendly because the owner sets the tone for the business. The owner herself is genuine, kind and truly wants you to have a good experience.  Her efforts pay off with the incredible cleanness of the rooms and the friendliness of the staff.  Finally, it is important to note that the beds are very well cared for.  The bulbs are regularly (often) changed to ensure you get the maximum experience.  This is a lovely place to visit and an excellent place to get tan.

I'll go with 5 stars. I really enjoyed the pulled pork sandwich which has guava BBQ sauce, carrot slaw and fried egg on a brioche bun. Tastes as good as it sounds. The seasoned fries were also very good and they gave me a lot of them. My friend ordered the cavatelli, which is a pasta/sausage dish that had too much of a lemony taste. Since she didn't love it, they took it off the bill. That was a pleasant surprise. The service was attentive for the most part. The decor is really nice and the outdoor balcony is a relaxing place to eat. Prices are decent too.

After several days driving by this place I decided to give it a try. Inside you will find a variety of sweets and a nice food/drink menu. 
Tried 2 of their multilayer crepe cakes, the egg tarts, the chicken sandwich, the steak sandwich, and the coconut bread. 
I wasn't a fan of the cakes because they weren't sweet enough for me, but if you don't like a super sweet cakes, these are a must-try. The rest of my order was delicious. The coconut bread was moist and fluffy similar to  "pan de coco". The egg tarts were a hit. And the sandwiches satisfying.  I will go back for more!

If you want the full Nashville tourist experience on Broadway then you have to stop in for a visit to Robert's Western World for the old school vibe and classic honky tonk music offered up here.  There are plenty of newer and more "modern" spots to visit on Broadway but there are few of the old classics like this left so make sure to visit and see a little bit of what Nashville used to be like before the population explosion.

We eat at a lot of Indian restaurants. Being from the UK we find most US curry houses quite lame and bland. I would say the Bindi is definitely stand out and I really like what they have done with the fusion menu. Sure its pricey but given the quality and thought that has gone into the unique selection of dishes I would say it's worth every cent. For two of us we spent about $100 without tip for starters, entrees and 1 desert. We brought a long a bottle of Rum (its BYOB) and they served us a very nice mixer (mango sharbat). We should have gone for the nimbu-pani (Indian style pomegranate-ginger lemonade) which was what the waitress recommended. The mango mixer was very nice but after a while was a bit sweet and sickly .... well she did warn us. I have never come across this before and its a nice concept. High quality cocktails but for a very reasonable price. 

The service is good and the decor modern and stylish. Location great. It's cash only but no problem, there is an ATM at the pizza joint two doors down. The food was yummy and very well cooked. I started with the ghee poached lobster pani puri which was very different to usual puri. The puri was made into 5 tasty little parcels, very unique. My Wife had the sindhi eggplant a gorgeous little vegetarian curry. Entree follow ups were just as good. I had the lamb two ways and the lamb was cooked to perfection and full of great flavors. My wife had the seafood goozoo which was kind of like and Indian Gumbo. Very tasty, but not as good as the lamb. Which was stand out. For desert I had the vanilla bean panna cotta. Very nice. All in all great, only comment would be everything is a touch over-salted. 

Gourmet and up-market Indian food with a twist? I'm sold! Don't expect large quantities of bland curry. Do expect some very unique and tasty Indian dishes. Will be back for sure.

I give this place a 5 for concept and a 3 for execution, for an average of 4 stars. 

The walls are a little too stark, the wait for food was a little too long, the tables were a little too close together, the portions were a little too small, and prices were a little too high. My eggs benedict was good, but not out of this world. My matcha (green tea) with soymilk was amazing though! 

However, I'm glad there's a place like this in Indianapolis - green, healthy, local, organic, classy food. There can't be many places in town where you can get blooming teas - those things are the epitome of class. With some minor improvements, Tulip Noir could easily be a 4 or 5 star place.

2nd time getting veggie wrap. 1rst time was amazing. Today's was absolutely horrible. First veggie wrap had spinach this had none. This is filled with lettuce! An onion here or an mushroom there! There was no seasoning so I'm using a salt packet now. Honestly this meal isn't worth a 5 min write-up. I called back to let the gentleman know that this wrap wasn't good at all. He said, "thanks". I try to give black businesses my support but this is what I get in exchange. I paid $10 for lettuce wrapped in a tortilla. Needless to say, getting it right some of the time is not what I'm interested in... Get this... I actually told the guy wearing the Islam necklace that I review their meals on line! And he he still didn't offer to replace. He needs to ask Allah or whoever he prays to - to open his 3rd eye. Maybe then he could have seen there was no salt going onto the grill when he was cooking. And that he was missing half the veggies! Never again.

After taking my daughter to see her doctor in LA we needed gas and to use the restroom. I am so sick of places not allowing the use of the restroom. You cannot catch COVID from a toilet seat. I will not fill up here again! I'll take my $50 a week somewhere that allows us use of the facility.

Flor de Maíz is the latest "Los Agaves" success! The menu is comprised of traditional dishes from Oaxaca. If you like ceviche or mole, you need to try Flor de Maiz. The specialty drinks are also amazing, I am usually a beer drinker but when you Visit this restaurant try their specialty drinks, you won't regret it. Both the food and drinks have very unique and bold flavors. Going to visit this place often...

One of my few afghan experiences. This is a very small place but parking was easy for dinner and we sat right down. We had a wonderful server help walk us through the menu. She even threw in some bonuses so we could try even more for our first visit!

Pashtoon salad appetizer, 3 different lamb entrees, and baklava made for an excellent meal for everyone at our table.  Only real negative was between pita and rice it was very starchy. You can just take home/split it for two meals though. 

I'll definitely be returning. Wonderfully cooked lamb, big portions, and 10% yelp discount? Great way to branch out (especially if you already like Greek or Indian food).  Extra star for being St. Louis' lone afghan place. Support diversity!

Stumbled upon Stockyard after seeing an Instagram post from Eater. After looking at Yelp, I was shocked to see that such a highly rated lunch spot existed only ONE block from my office and I had never heard of it. When I walked over, I realized why I never noticed it before. It's right next to an out of business Chinese spot and has nearly no sign. 

The food was delicious, the sides are HUGE and everything tastes homemade. Its clear that the chef puts a lot of thought into designing unique and delicious food. Between my coworkers and I, we had the burger, the spicy fried chicken sandwich, the onion rings, the fried potatoes and the brussell sprouts. Everything was perfectly greasy and HUGE. Well worth the $4 for each side.

Looking forward to trying breakfast!

So i placed an order that had a total more than 85$ and it got late. so i called the costumer service and while i was with the person she asked for my order # which i gave it to her and surprising she said the order got cancelled. it got canceled because i didn't answer the phone, and i was with her on the phone and my cellphone was working and i didn't receive any call. she said the person called me 7:43 and i told her that i didn't receive any call. and she said that i have to order again to get my order. i told her that i won't order i want my money she said it'll take 3-5 business days, and i asked her what if i don't get my money she said i will. after that she asked "how was the service today?" i said "i didn't like it at all" she didn't even care and closed the line on my face... THANK YOU GOPUFF FOR THE BAD AND DISRESPECTFUL SERVICE.

my family of four visited this place on 2/23/18 and had a horrible experience. we were charged for food that we did not receive and when we explained our problem they refused to take it off of our bill. my husband decided not to argue anymore and paid the bill. we will not ever return to this restaurant. we were charged an extra $8 to share an hibachi dinner, then my husband ordered an extra side of noodles for hisself and was only given his shared portion not the extra side he ordered and they insisted that was his extra side portion he asked for. so we paid for an extra side of noodles $3.95 that we did not receive. he asked what the extra $8 charge was for and was told he don't get extra food for sharing that was just for him to get a plate. horrible service and will never return!!!!!!
First time. Got the spicy pork tacos. Went straight to flavor town. Can't wait to try more.

Love love love this restaurant! Friendly service and delicious food. Ribeye is always delicious. They also have select meals for only $9.99 if you dine between 4-6pm Monday - Thursday. Hot fresh rolls are alway waiting your arrival yummy

awful experience here.  got injured during training and trainer had audacity to treat me like I had no idea what I was talking about.  I have had an ACL replacement since.  check trainer credentials and make sure you are not working out with just any meathead off the street.  Never got an ounce of customer service or support from the place...wanted refund on my class and trainer and manager kept handing me off to one another.  Rip off...
I am at a great Gym now with a highly qualified trainer.  So glad I left here.

Big Mistake. The only good thing was we waited less time than we were told  blooming onion was ok the spices were not tasty, wings were meaty but not tasty again the spices were yuk. 3 different entrees salmon not good, chicken, so so, and prime rib again the spices were awful. Potato was terrible, loaded with butter sour cream and cheese and bacon but dry, old tasting. Even the bread was dry and stale tasting.  Gave it a try and lost $100 plus tip to find out should have went to a Texas Riadhouse. Way better and cheaper.

I am a fan of this hospital. The Staff is always friendly and helpful when I need help getting around in the hospital. I like that fact that the hospital is always clean and neat. The parking is FREE and they even have FREE Valet parking. I am from West Virginia and we don't have that service for FREE in Charleston at the area medical centers. 

I have had to come here for blood work in the lab, some xrays and some testing. They were always fast and friendly which is great customer services. When I need questions answered they either take care of it or find me someone who can. I like this hospital.
Awesome food! Highly recommend the bacon nachos.  And super friendly staff.

HORRIBLE karaoke song selection and HORRIBLE attitude.  "If the song you want to sing is not on this list, it probably sucks" is on their SPARSE song list.  Let me tell you something:  It is your catalog that sucks.  You may want to get some variety before you cop such a garbage attitude.  You are NOT as good as you think you are.

I guess there is no such thing as a bad Sonoran dog, but they are certainly not all created equal. 

I will just be brief and say that this is the least tasty Sonoran hot dog that I've had since I moved to Tucson.  If you are in the area and craving a a dog, I suggest driving a bit farther south.

The pastrami sandwich is worth every calorie.  It was soooo good I might have to go back tonight for another one.  The service was amazing, I sat outside and enjoyed the view while eating as slow as possible. Go there now.

I've been here a couple times before and the service at this location has been horrendous. However, this time was different. The service in the dining room was the saving grace. 

The hostess greeted us, sat us instantly and was very friendly. The waitress was efficient and a sweetheart. Everything came out correctly in a timely fashion (which is unusual at this place in my past experiences) and she always had a smile on her face. 

The food was mediocre. I ordered the sliders. They claim to come with a sauce, but I didn't see any at all. Not even on the bottom of the bun. The sliders looked like they made one burger and sliced it with a blindfold on. One of the sliders were gigantic and the bottom of the bun was a tiny morsel of bread. Another slider was the opposite, the burger was tiny and the bun was huge. It was evident the cook didn't give a crap. If it were a Saturday night dinner rush and the kitchen was slammed, I would let it slide. (No pun intended) This was a Wednesday night and the dining room was about a quarter full. 

Another thing, my menu was disgusting. It was sticky and covered in some sort of substance. I'm assuming a customer previously ate with it on the table and spilled something on it. It was so gross that I quickly decided on an entree just so I wouldn't have to look through the menu anymore. 

The drinks we ordered during dinner were delicious and cheaper than what I remembered. The games were the highlight. (per usual) My boyfriend and I were planning on ordering drinks from the bar in the game room, but it took about 5 minutes for one of the two bartenders to acknowledge our existence. The bar was not that busy and I have received faster service when they've had a full bar. Finally when one of the bartenders (older blonde woman) acknowledged us we ordered waters. Normally I tip a dollar when I order just a water from the bar because it's free and they are still doing me a service. The woman looked at us as if we were a burden to her and continued what she was doing. A minute or two later she proceeds to use the cups to scoop out the ice. Working in the business myself I know that this is a no-no whether it's plastic or glass. We decided against not ordering any alcoholic drinks due to poor service and the fear of cutting my mouth with a piece of glass. On top of that we could smell the nasty odor from the drains while leaving (smelled similar to a nursing home bathroom) and the floors of the bar looked filthy. Definitely never ordering a drink from the game room next time I go back.

3 shrimp... 3 shrimp.
The man taking my wife's order upsaled her from veggie pad Thai to shrimp... And they gave us... 3 shrimp.

How dare you? That's unacceptable.

On top of that, there were 0 veggies in the padthai. So what we had was a plate of barely seasoned noodles.

Seriously, so absurd.

The short ribs had hard, chewy, inedible fatty bits.

The curry was a soup.

What a disappointment. I added a star because the food we got wasn't gross... Except for the hard, fatty ribs. Those were gross.

If you want to invest in an electric bike, Pedego is the only way to go. The Dunedin Pedego service is exemplary! The bikes are free for the first hour of rental and you can try various models becore you buy! I love my boomerang Pedego. #PedegoDunedin

Best place for a sandwich in Nashville hands down. I believe it's stupid to pay for something you can easily make at home (salad, smoothies, pasta and sandwiches) BUT Mitchell's is way too good, I've had the asian tofu sandwich, the avocado BLT, seitan supreme, tuna sandwich and the chicken salad sandwich and they're all amazing. They all come with a pickle and everything is better with a pickle. They have great cold brew coffee, kombucha and beers on tap, they also sell to go sides which I've heard good things about but have never had myself. They use fresh, high quality ingredients and the customer service is quick, friendly and overall great. The online ordering is easy to use, it's also easy to phone in an order ahead of time. My only wish is that one day they would make a meatball sub (but if you're wanting one go to tower deli) but other than that they're simply the best
Son loves this place. Can't get him to go anywhere else. Faye is terrific. She is knowledgeable, creative and always figures out a way to fit me in.

Stopped to get our free growler through Yelp (only on Mondays and Tuesdays) and ended up enjoying this place. The selection is huge and varietal. Friendly service, informative and busy on a Tuesday night. Free samples: ended up tasting the summer grist and lager - both delicious! Decided to go with the lager because the summer grist only filled a 32oz growler :( We only stayed for like 15 minutes because we were on a schedule. Wish we could have hung around!
Perfect spot to get a cold beer on a hot summer day in the French Quarter.

Stunning boutique hotel.  Rooms are beyond expectations and those bathrooms- OMG.  The only reason I'm taking away a star is the lack of front desk customer service. I dont expect anyone to open doors but to be on your phone all the time and sitting down not greeting guest is very rude.  We were there 3 days an after the 3rd attempt at saying hello to them I stopped and didn't even acknowledge they were there (like they did me).  Bar we as cute, loud but cute and again not very helpful or friendly.  I'd probably stay again only for the rooms/bathrooms not for service.  The location was ok, sorta hidden and dark but overall ok.

This is my favorite spot to eat in Tampa! I have never been disappointed here. The tuna tar tar is a delicious appetizer. I also love their parmesan crusted chicken caesar salad and their macaroni and cheese is to die for! If you are over 21 you must order the cucumber gimlet- so good! The service is always 5 stars! Definitely recommend.
Glad to see this place open for breakfast and lunch, since we were sad to see A Great Location close. Good menu at a reasonable price. Friendly staff and great service.Haven't had a bad meal here.

Tourist trap gumbo! I should've known better but it was a short walk from my hotel. I ordered the seafood gumbo and was disappointed! How can u serve seafood gumbo w a few tiny shrimp and 1 tiny crab claw in New Orleans?! This is shopping mall style gumbo for ppl who don't know. Please change the name of this place.

One of the 3 must-go brunch places in Philadelphia. (Sabrina's and Honey's are the other 2). I've found the South Philly location to have slightly less wait, better parking, and equally delicious food to the Northern Liberties location. No reservations and your party must be all present in order to be seated, but once you're seated service is quite good.  Most of their food has pork-less and vegan friendly options. But you can order the meat and pork-full options like I do. No matter what you order, it's almost impossible to go wrong. Cash only but there's an atm on location.
Friday night out. It's been years since I've been here but it still feels like home.  Great drinks and the best roast beef sandwiches around!
Went here for a soft opening. Food was really good and would recommend. Need to try the soup dumplings.
Love this restaurant the food was amazing and so were the drinks. I was driving looking for a place to enjoy my taco and tequila Tuesday and I think I found my spot from now on.

Occhiali Eyewear has the best selection of high-end sunglass and eyewear in Santa Barbara!
The lady was knowledgeable and helpful to check my Kate spade sunglasses.
If you're looking for great glasses and top-quality customer service, this is it!
Thank you for your service!
I will definitely recommend this place.

I have been a regular customer for many years and am extremely disappointed. I grew up eating Italias food and truly missed it when I moved away. When I moved back, I was happy to know that I would have a great pizza place to order my favorites from again. Last week I treated myself and ordered the Chicken Francaise, a $17.00 dinner with delivery, but I argue to myself that it is worth it because you get two huge pieces of chicken and some pasta. Once again it's expensive, but I feel worth it because I also have lunch for the next day.  My husband orders me food once a week because I'm unable to cook on this day. Today, my husband ordered ordered the same thing and tipped the driver $5 because "He didn't have change" which I didn't mind at that point because I was excited about my meal. When I opened the container there was only one large piece of chicken. I've never called and complained about other mistakes, but for a $22 meal I felt like I was robbed. A woman answered and I explained the situation to which she said that the piece of chicken was the same size of two pieces. I explained to her that that was not the case. She then became a little snarky and told me that I was given one piece because they pounded it out and made it bigger. I can assure you that the one piece is the same size of one piece from last week. I was taken back by her behavior and responded "That's your answer?" To which case she hung up on me. I've worked in the industry and people want consistency, to be treated with respect and to get what they pay for. It is unfortunate that we will be shopping for a place that can fulfill these basic requirements. I can say that we will miss there food, but can't be concerned about poor accountability. Giving two stars for the quality, losing major points for treating a "regular" so brashly, inconsistency and money lost:(

The friendliest, most cheerful staff. Made my morning!

The cappuccino with almond milk was nothing extraordinary and a little pricey, but looking forward to trying more from them in the future.

If they have belligerent customers All other customers suffer- worst service ever had to get up 4 times to get cutlery, plate, ask for another drink and a to go box and the bill - mgr comped $4 off a $50 tab WoW! Thanks for nothing next time go home and order s pizza

This place does a great job putting lifts on shoes for leg length discrepancies.  He uses a lighter material for the lift so that you are not carrying a heavy shoe as you walk.  Customer service is A+ and the turn around is quick.  I even brought in Birkenstock sandals with a broken strap and they sewed a new one on matching the color.

The actual nursery is beautiful and has a nice selection of plants. However, the employees and overall customer service is AWFUL. 

I am a novice gardener and have been there several times in the last few months while starting an indoor herb and succulent garden.  There is an older woman in the greenhouse that has a rough attitude and does her best to ignore you. I explained to her that I was starting a garden for the first time and had a few questions about plant selection and care. Her answers were short and I ended up researching my questions online. 

The second time I went to pick up a gardenia. I went outside to their flower section and asked a male employee if he could show me where they were. He told me to look in the greenhouse. After a 15 minute search, I still couldn't locate the plant. I went to the register and the same employee was there. When I asked if he could show me specifically where the gardenia was, he looked annoyed and said "oh, well now that I think of it, we don't have any". It seemed more like he just didn't want to take the time to show me. 

The woman working the register took my name and said she would order the plant. The next day I got a call from the rough lady from greenhouse who said they had had the plant yesterday and said I just didn't know where to look. 

After having the plant for a week, all of the buds and a few leaves  turned yellow and dropped off. I called to ask if I was doing something wrong and was told that I needed to give it more water. The person I spoke with said if that didn't work, then I could exchange the plant. Watering made the problem worse, and I soon noticed gnats. The gnats started affecting all of my other plants. 

I called a second time and was told to bring the plant in to exchange it. Again, the greenhouse lady was not friendly and simply told me that the plant had a lot of problems. She suggested neem oil to help with the pests. I asked if could exchange it as I was told I could, and she told me no, that's not the policy. 

If you are an experienced gardener and need no assistance - this might be a great option for your plant needs. Otherwise, AVOID!

Not surprised about the multiple 5 Star ratings for this amazing flower gallery. They have been part of the tradition of my wife's birthday for four years now ... back when the shop was on Spruce Street ... always anemones ... always exceeding expectations ... easy ordering ... friendly service ... reliable delivery ... and the flowers, the arrangements are amazing. Thank you, guys ... keep up the good work ... we've got more birthdays to look forward to.
Price is reasonable. Chicken pho is good. Spring roll is good too. If you never know what to eat, you can always come here and get pho. Fast service too.

I must admit I did not read any reviews before going. 

Well as for me I had a wonderful experience. My room was very clean and modern. The staff was very friendly to me. I love the fact that there is a UNO (restaurant) adjacent to the hotel so going over there & having a few drinks I could just easily walk back to the hotel (no drinking and driving). From my room I could look out my window and see where my vehicle was parked. I have went to various hotels/hotel chains so small things can make a big difference in my experience and ratings. 

Not being a local I loved that the area is populated and there is a ton of stores right nearby. 

I went in and sanitized with my Lysol spray, inspected the bed/furniture (very clean inspection), and sleep well.

Hey, do you like Fish + Chips? Do you like Beers on Cask? Do you like English Pubs?  How about you take a cab, ride a train, maybe not rollerblade, hop on your bicycle, skateboard or just walk...and go to this address:

124 S 18th St  
Philadelphia, PA 19103

Don't mind the name or that it is Stephen Starr owned.  Sit by the fire, drink some good beer and eat some (generally) authentic and delicious English Pub Food.

Went there for lunch with friends.  I noticed they changed the menu since I'd been there.  I ordered their Oriental Chicken Salad.  The only thing Asian about it was the noodles that were in it.  It also came with mandarin orange slices in it that actually tasted like they were sitting in an oven and had gone sour.  The menu itself has not been updated to reflect changes except in the prices going up and a sharpie blacking out what is no longer available on the menu.  About the only thing going for the restuarant right now is it's name.  I probably won't be there again unless they get a new manager, owner or chef.

Well, the food here was amazing (5 stars) and the prices were pretty reasonable compared to other Tapas placed I've been.  Unfortunately, the service was quite poor. I'm hoping they are still just figuring out the service side of the business. We'll be back, but with time to spare and sans children.
I've yet to have something bad from here. The pizza,cheese steaks and tuna are my personal favs. One bad thing i can say is that the wings don't come with bc which is strange.
Order the pig mac and the pork belly sandwich along with the mac n cheese and key lime pie.  Everything was so good.  Don't pass this restaurant up.

Really debated sending out this review but it's necessary...This was not good. Had the chicken finger plate and tried three sides: potato salad, pimento Mac n cheese, and Cole slaw. The potato salad and Cole slaw were so bland. It was just potatoes with mayonnaise and then shredded cabbage with mayonnaise..which doesn't sound that bad, but again SO bland. The pimento Mac n cheese had a small curly dark hair in it....but I've heard it's actually good. The chicken was subpar. I would not recommend this hot chicken in Nashville.

It's slightly cramped compared to the west coast H marts that I'm used to, but hey overall it's pretty awesome. Especially love the food court. It's a nice, low-key way to have Korean food. They only give you like 3 out of 2000 of the little plates/appetizers when you eat there.

Thursday evening 7 of us tried to go to Canyon Café for dinner. There were empty tables but still would be an hour wait. We asked about separating into two tables but it would be as long. We gave up and went to Cardwell's.

Okay, bottom line up front: just drive the extra 10 minutes and go enjoy the nice Casino (Casino Del Sol). 

Smokey, small, and ehhhh food. (We didn't win either but honestly I don't expect too. We just like to play.)

I was going to give it one star , but decided on  because it had great RV parking.

They have HAD to have a change in management or something, because seeing the old reviews is not at all what I've experienced! All the doors are clean, and the blankets and sheets are much more up to date then in the pictures. We've been staying in the King Deluxe for about $50 a night, which compared to other hotels we've stayed at is a steal!! The air is pumping when we walked in already, there's a cute automated nightlight near the bathroom at night, the set up when we walked in was really nice, there is HBO, free easy access WIFI and the desk that's in the room has lights in it, and electrical sockets. Another plus is when we left for breakfast we put the little maid sign out of the door and when we got back the whole place was spotless again. We are young, and seems like we're always on a budget now I won't go anywhere else in the area! The staff up front is always really nice also. There is laundry hookups, and they have toothpaste, and plastic silver wear up front. I would recommend!

Oh my goodness this place is delicious! I was afraid I wouldn't be able to get an order tonight because I've heard how popular this place has become and sometimes you can't get through on the phone. Tonight was or lucky night. Ordered a stuffed steak pizza and was ready right when they said it would be. It was huge and tasty! There were tons of toppings which made it very filling. Can't wait for future orders to try the rest of the menu. Also, my husband is in the restaurant business and he couldn't stop raving about how clean it was!

Ho.ly.shit. This place is amazing. Definitely exceeded my expectations! My sister and I shared the lobster Benedict and kahlua banana French toast and we feel like we went to heaven.

The lobster Benedict had buttery lobster pieces, and perfectly poached eggs (egg porn videos, yes) atop soft English muffins. And the hollandaise sauce was not too strong, great flavor! It's a little pricey but to me it was well worth it.

The French toast was lovely as well. Nice, thick toast with the right amount of crispy-ness and softness. The kahlua sauce is amazeballs. 

All the other food looked really good too, and they have pastries/cakes on display by the register. This little cafe has so much to offer, you wouldn't be able to tell just by looking at it! Wish we had one down in Orange County T__T

I have been here a few times since moving to St. Louis from Phoenix.  I was looking forward to spoiling myself and family with some warm, stylish gear.  Every time I've been in there, though, they have been inattentive, unhelpful, and down right ignoring me.  Yesterday I asked if they had backpacks, and the guy rolled his eyes and pointed to a wall of backpacks.  Needless to say, I would rather spend my money elsewhere on North Face gear where I'm treated better, for example Nordstrom or Macy's.  I give them 2 stars instead of the 1 they truly deserve because their stuff is sort of cool.

We paid over $17000 for a new HVAC system..within a year on the hottest day it broke down,and we had to wait 2 days for service.The same has happened this year,and waited 2 days and semi working,but can't get temp Lowe than 80! Told we have to wait 5 days til after holiday to get service.Went on line and got emergency appointment for tomorrow.
Still under 2 year guarantee. Guy came out checked everything and put mind at rest.Do not call as will be put off til later date..went on line and got next day appointment.Should not have to wait if no poair conditioning in heat wave when under guarantee,and if skip telephone appointment did not have to!

I love our Farmers Markets and have been a customer for decades. Gladden and Sons is even more special and worthy of your attention. Don't go in with a list but come out with delights. A good business with (almost) bygone values.

Definitely a fan of this place.  Good sausages.  Pretty good kielbasa (almost as good as Lachoiwecz in Bridesburg).  Awesome crew that works there.  Hoping I walk in there one day to be able to score some boudin noir.  Lots of different sausage choices too (bacon sausage?  yes please!).
My family and I are picky AF. Sauce is on point. The Stromboli and X-Pepperoni pizza we ordered was delicious! Four people give a well deserved thumbs up

This is a great example of a local favorite. We had the Hot & Sassy burger and the catfish. The candy yams are to die for, they are just like momma makes. Finally the Sweet Tea is grandma style, but they also have favored such as Mango and Peach! It's a great atmosphere with jazz style art on the walls along with Great music playing while you sit and relax with Friends!!! Wonderful food spot

Our experience with Ashley's has been a joke.  The guest response team has been no help at all, they call you tell you they can't do something then hang up.  The store has tried to help but there is a huge break down between the store and delivery departments.  It took about 2 months to get our couches and about 3 rescheduled deliveries with little notice after we had already taken off from work.  We still have a dining room table to get as well as some other little furniture but we will go anywhere but Ashley's for those even if it costs a little bit extra.

I frequent this location. I love the blackened salmon and yukon mashed Potatoes. I made Mother's Day reservations and was thinking the wine was still half priced given the advertised information but was told this was not the case. I didnt make a scene of it and paid full price but they should be clear ahead of time its for holidays including those listed. The crab cakes need to be cooked longer and the salmon today was undercooked as well. Normally the salmon is cooked perfectly but today both my mother and I had undercooked salmon filets.

I also emailed the chef/manager after he responded to this yelp review but didnt receive a response.
Quick food and a wonderful wine and spirit menu. However, a little pricey for 'not so authentic' mexican.

Our Airbnb hostess actually recommended that we check out this community of small, local businesses while staying at her East Nashville abode. The Shoppes were a quick five minute drive and are near a score of other popular restaurants and attractions, so we popped over to check them out.

We parked easily on the street and started exploring. The complex sort of reminded me of an outdoor market with stalls or micro shops. Each business has its own personality, but there's a flow with the shared walkway and seating sprinkled about.

We went into most of them, but the most memorable were Whiskey Water with its fun items dedicated to my favorite libation; Abode Mercantile where we bought bread mix to enjoy at home; and Konadu Body Care which carries the most incredible bath and body products. Konadu also won our award for nicest and most helpful shopkeeper.

After shopping, we hopped down the street for a root beer float at The Soda Parlour. There's so much to see, do, eat, and drink in East Nashville. Can't wait for the next road trip!

What can I say?  I was in Philly for 2.5 days, and had Jim's twice.  It's that good.  

Jim's has the best cheesesteak by far in Philly.  The first time I got the Whiz with mushrooms.  I lucked out and was at the point in the line where a fresh slab of meat was thrown on the griddle.  I was more than happy to wait the additional 5 mins for some fresh juicy chopped steak.  It was worth it.  Each bite had juice flowing everywhere.  I came back the next day, and ordered the whiz with mushrooms and peppers.  Equally delicious and juicy.

I will definitely be back.

PRO TIP:  Eat the first half over the 2nd half, allowing the delicious juices to drip onto the second half.  You won't regret it.
This place makes me happy to live in East Falls! Great food and authentic dining environment.

This bed bath beyond is in a great location this bed bath and beyond is a great location for me. I recommend the store Because the people are very friendly, knowledgeable and will work with you to find a great selection. However you do need to use Coupons since they're a little on the pricey side

We only had an overnight business trip to Philadelphia and wanted to see as much of the city as we could. We hopped on the big bus and had a great time. Tour guide was phenomenal and informative. We were very satisfied with our experience. Thanks!

Overall it was an ok dining experience.  Food was ok and the service was pretty good.  I had the broil pot and didn't care for the oysters and lobster.  The crab legs was very good.  If I dined hear again I would get the 2lbs of crab legs.  All people at my table received desert that was included with the meal.

I had high expectations for Tavern...perhaps too high.

I tried the Tavern Burger as it had been recommended to me so many times. The "meltaway" bun was the highlight, but everything else fell flat. The meat had a strange (to me) taste that I couldn't quite put my finger on. It may have been the rib eye/filet beef mix, but as I like both of those cuts I have a hard time believing that was the culprit. I couldn't even finish it, which as a burger lover is extremely rare.

The side of fries were relatively standard yet plentiful.

The service was okay. I would have expected better from an upscale restaurant, but it was sufficient. The atmosphere inside the restaurant was great -- definitely my favorite part of the meal.

I'm certainly willing to give Tavern another chance, but I'll go for something other than the burger.

This is a great bike shop.  As a beginning biker, I really appreciate how helpful they are.  I have taken two bikes here for some work, and have always been pleased at the amount they charge for their services.  I also attended a bike repair class here this past week free of charge.  I think it is great that they do things like this.  All of the employees I have encountered here have been very friendly.

The bikes, accessories, and apparel are all a little pricey and probably more targeted toward serious bikers as they seem to be high end brands, but they are pretty comparable to any bike shop.  They also sell used bikes for the more price conscious consumers.
After last years review we decided to give it a try again. Tonights food was on point. Thank you for the great customer service and making it right

I drive past this restaurant pretty much every day. So, I took my daughter there for breakfast. As a server myself, I understand the business of a Saturday.  The server wasn't that personable, and didn't really seem to care about how out food really was. We had to ask for a kids menu for my daughter. Her oatmeal was very blan. Even after dumping brown sugar in it, and adding  more sugar, it was still blan. And very soupy. If you like your oats thick, you should ask for it this way  So she didn't eat it. She ordered a cinnamon roll instead. I had the the steak breakfast, which was pretty good. But the country potatoes were cold. I think i will keep driving past this restaurant in the future.

Wonderful food 
Great prices
Very friendly 
Come taste the food
Great location 
Close to USF

The food was absolutely amazing and the staff was even better than that. Really enjoyed this place and will be going back very soon. I'm thinking tomorrow. I want to try some other things on the menu but enjoyed what I got so much this time I might just reorder the same things next time I'm there.

Always busy.  Awesome seafood.  Laid back atmosphere.   Can't beat it! 

Shrimp and corn chowder is killer.  It's got real nice heat.  Shrimp and crawfish boils are awesome and messy.

Service is always good. 

If you go during a peak lunch or dinner be ready to wait 15-30 minutes.  This place packs them in all the time.

Just that old town and old fashion barbershop. Wayne goes out of his way to cut and trim your hair. Shop is that old time look with memorabilia on the walls.  Time spent waiting for your number called enjoy the signs and posters. Great price and value.  Early in the day they are packed but later in the say it's walk in and sit down or your cut.  They also do lady haircuts.

Found this gem on Yelp while searching for a place to have Bloody Marys and lunch on a Saturday.  We sat at the bar, waited on by Julie who was awesome.  Fast, friendly service.  They make their own Bloody Mary mix which was DELICIOUS (I would like to give 10 stars if I could!).  We had the Smoked Mahi fish spread and OMG was amazing.  It was by far the best fish spread we've had since moving to FL...more fish than filling so great flavor and you really get what you pay for.  We chatted with the owner Rick who is a great guy and offered us samples of the smoked salmon fish spread and smoked ribs.  Again, DELICIOUS!  We appreciate any place that makes what we call "craft food".  We will be back, often!

Very cool concept- they could've definitely done more with it though. The food was fresh and hot. The pizza was amazing! Also tried their fries and the California cheesesteak- awesome! Wait was reasonable, service was good. Pretty cool place- was a little dirty. Not bad though. We'll definitely go back.

I love this place. I'm very picky about my nails and have shopped around for a long time. Other places charge you an arm and a leg and do a crappy job. Kim does a really good job and takes pride in her work. She is very detailed oriented and kind. They have recently repainted their walls and got new massage chairs. Because they are so affordable, I'm planning on going to them on a weekly basis now. Don't go to big nail places where you're just another person paying them a lot of money for poor quality, bad attitude and worse (talking about you in another language). Trust me! visit First Tip Nails and you won't go anywhere else.

Service was very slow but probably because they were training someone new.  Appetizer was great (fried kale) but the entrees were so-so...pizza and 2 pasta dishes.  My daughters pizza was over cooked...black in some spot was fine but the crust was all black.  Maybe just a bad night because we loved it last time we came.  Beautiful decor

Don't bother ordering from this unpublished place. They send their jerk people to leave flyers ta hotels and these people are not background checked and from different parts of country and known to enter rooms if left open. The food is frozen and terrible at best.These little places have a larger menu than Cheesecake factory and NONE of it is worthy of payment.They have a no refund policy and god knows how many complaints we get of the delivery guys eating their food.
These are the worst places to order from at any hotel delivery.Stay with the Poppa Johns or pizza hut to avoid these crap food.

Everyone enjoyed brunch.  Sons had the pancake special. Wife had the mash substituted sausage for ground beef.  And I had tuna melt with grilled onions.   Next time we are in Santa Barbara we will return

I am a bit of a foodie in Philadelphia and I would say that this is one of the best places to eat in Philadelphia. Myself and my boyfriend shared 4 entrees: the ravioli, the pork belly, the chicken, and the short rib. First of all, the short rib is by far the best short rib I have ever had in my entire life. Second of all, chicken is usually basic for me but this chicken was out of this world. Lastly, the ravioli were so good that we wanted twice as many (I think there were 5, we used this as our starter). The chefs really know what they're doing. Carrot cake for dessert was good but nothing special. I would skip next time. 
Amelia was our server and she was wonderful. Her coworkers helped prebus and get extra brioche when we asked. They really worked as a team. 

Check was a bit pricey but OMG it was worth it. I can't wait to go back in the summer so that we can eat in the garden.
Sorcery!!! Only way I can explain this fantastic Pho. My personal favorites are #28 and #21, accompanied with an order of spring rolls. This pho I can eat anytime of the year.

After a night of drinking, comfort food hit the spot! Great homecooked breakfast, nothing fancy. I cleared a plate of veggie omelet with southern grits, sampled their calla cake with a good cup of hot coffee. I agree the wait staff was less than attentive or quick, but when you get their attention, they're friendly.
Excellent place to wash off trip from Michigan!  Definitely recommend!!!  Ready now for Florida.

So I've heard nothing but good things about this place then go in to have a piercing done and get told that they double booked my appointment and because the person who also booked at my time showed up before me I need to reschedule. Also received the WORST service from the people at the front desk, they were complete assholes about the whole thing and did nothing to make me even want to return to do it. Awful service even if they are good at what they do they should have WAY better service than what was provided and that service alone will be the sole reason I tell people to never go here. Ever. AWFUL CUSTOMER SERVICE! You guys really should re-evaluate your front desk people to more hospitable people. I would have rescheduled for another day if they weren't complete dicks about it.

Just hope you get Chad as your server. 
Amazeballs meatloaf tower and plantains...what more could you want. Also, their deals are BOMB! 2 for 1 rum drinks?! HELLO MAI TAIS!

Have to update this review again. I came here for the second time since I wrote the last review. Remember the issue I had the first time with this place was the fact that they dry cleaned all of my seams about a half inch from the pant seam on the side of my pants. I expressed how much I disliked this and when I received a call from the store after seeing my review they told me they updated my account in the computer so that they only make the crease down the middle of my leg, great. Well I went to pick up $93 worth of dry cleaning for this week and next this morning and everything was done incorrectly, again. I called right away and the lady told me to come back and they will do everything free of charge. I can't bring all of my work clothes back- I need something to wear. This is so frustrating as I plan on everything being done correctly.
All around excellent food & drink, friendly staff and great atmosphere. Inside or outdoor seating with a beautiful view is a great option as well.

There are very few places I would drive an hour to eat at. I really enjoy all of their food and the service is great. They are busy because of how amazing they are so I suggest calling ahead and making reservations. They do try their best to fit you in if they can. All around good food and service. Love that its a full course meal!!

Campo was absolutely amazing. We sat outside to enjoy the view of the water. Our server was Anthony, who was absolutely amazing. Remembered us from months ago. 

We asked what was on the chefs special. They gave us 3 different option but the one the struck out to me was the Salmon in a puff pastry over mash potatoes. Something about salmon in a puff pastry was very interesting to me. I ordered it and wooow I was blown away. It was so good. The soft salmon with the crunch from the pastry and the savory mash potatoes. Highly recommend this spot.

Zia's was recommended to us by another family visiting St. Louis. What a gem. Everything we ordered was delicious. Started with toasted ravioli and fried mozzarella. Had Zia's salad, cannelloni, and chicken parmigiana. Staff was great and very friendly. We ended up purchasing their dipping oil and salad dressing.

Our two girls love it here. Being a product of an excellent public school I was skeptical of Waldorf education, thinking it was too "touchy-feely" and "crunchy granola." Now that I understand the basic philosophy of Waldorf, to let younger children learn from play and, before trying to cram a lot of data into them, help them develop their social skills, sense of community and respect, and connectedness with the natural world into which we've all been born and fit. When this healthy foundation has been established, and their little bodies finally have grown enough to grasp and integrate the data, they're ready to learn how to read and do math, etc. Our girls are not only getting an excellent  education but are growing into the savvy, well-rounded and happy women citizens of the world their caring parents know they'll be. And, let's not forget that successful, high achievers like the chairman of AmEx and a former NASA rocket scientist are products of a Waldorf education.

I purchased a 2015 Optima in February from Jermaine. He was extremely helpful and nice to work with. The service department on the other hand is horrible. My car started overheating and it turned out to be the fan. After being told I would have my car back in a couple of days, I finally received. It after about 10 days. I had to call several times as Steve didn't communicate what was happening and why the delay. I also requested a call from the service manager and never received a call from him. They had to order one more part that was supposed to be in stock in a week. Over two weeks later, I finally received a call. I have to schedule an appointment for that part and now the warning light is on again. I'm disappointed that I have a lemon and they aren't taking responsibility for all the issues the car is having already. I own a 2008 Hyundai with over 150k miles and have never had one issue.

Fast and perfect ... back patio with a patterned colored border.
Separate crews for prep, pouring, and finishing, completed on schedule.
They took special effort to clean up the entire area after each work day.
I'm very happy with the results.

Go to place for anything korean I feel. The menu covers pretty much everything korean related. Panchon is so much, like so many dishes as well as refillable and they really don't mind. If you order bbq they give you a free danjang jjigae! As well as a free pancake! Like great service. The sashimi is pretty much always fresh, one of the best places in Philly for fresh sashimi. Even for like a small order without bbq my go to would be the kkanpoonki, korean style fried chicken(boneless). The seasoning and portions for it are great and sauce is spot on, personally feel that it's better than soho for chicken! If they had wings on the normal menu they would be out of business in my opinion!

This is a family owned aquarium with all native fish.  It is very educational and fun for all ages.  They keep them in more native environments than the larger and more expensive tourist aquariums which reflects their dedication to care.  The feeding programs are excellent as well. You should ignore many of the below comments. In my view the negative points are minor, are made up by the personal touch and I'm sure their new facility will be incredible.
It was so mediocre service was good but the food was horrible. Very bland and just really weird

Let me begin by saying simply - I'm so glad I stopped into this place. We'll get to the food in just a second. The ambience of 101 Beer Kitchen is upscale, yet relaxed. I felt comfortable in a polo and jeans; but others were wearing hoodies and t-shirts. I expected a wait, so I called ahead and made a reservation. A friend decided to meet me. I told the hostess, and thought I would havw to wait for him to arrive - to my surprise she proceeded to take me to the table. Once seated, I immediately noticed they had one of my favorite beers "Founder's Red Rubaeus", I ordered it. When the drink came out, it was filled to the brim - a pleasant surprise. The menu is just one page front and back - but I'm sure you'll find something that fits your pallet. I ordered the Pecan Crusted Chicken without the Honey Mustard. The two large chicken breasts sit atop a heap of delicious mashed potatoes and green beans. Each bite was delicious until I realized I was full. I had enough to box up and have a second full meal with. I will be going back.

We live in Illinois, so had to cross the river to get my son's tattoo (he's 17).  We did some internet searches and looked through online portfolios.....other than that, it is the first time hearing of or stepping foot into the establishment.  Great environment, friendly staff.
Mandy, who greeted us and did all the paperwork and stuff, was super sweet, kind, attentive, and respectful.  
Side note that I find to be relevant when character is important as you read reviews: Actually overheard Mandy on a phone call with an obviously not so patient and nice person.  She handled it with grace and dignity.  She represented her employer well!
The artist, Andy, presented a perfect representation of what my son shared with him.  A very personal tattoo.  He made a few tweaks that were exactly what was needed.  Professional, respectful!
Very pleased with All Star Tattoo.  From start to finish, it couldn't have been a better experience.
Thank you!

I'm not sure why this is at 3.5 stars. It's the best basic breakfast diner I know of in the area.
If you're looking for something a bit different from bland omelettes and hash browns, and a bit of southwestern flavor this is a good bet.
It's mainly straight up diner fare but everything seems homemade and fresh.
I like their breakfast burritos. My son loves the biscuits and gravy.
Their salsa is always good.
Coffee is diner coffee. Meh, I wish they'd get something better.

Went there for my birthday, the service was terrible, we didn't have enough silverware and my husband had to get up three different times to find the waiter so we could get more water and other items we needed.  Also, we got charged incorrectly on the bill.  Then I left a special mug there that's been in the family for a long time and they lost it.  When I talked with the manager, he said he apologizes and prides himself on good customer service, told me he'd call me back and never did! Our bill was over $100, if I want crappy service I can get it for a lot less than that! Not going back! There's better Asian cuisine, Golden Flower is amazing and half the price!

I have made this place a regular lunch visit.  Absolutely love the Black Forest sandwich.  Fries are always seasoned just right.  Good place to watch a sporting event.  Oh and the waitresses are very friendly and professional.  If you like Pool this place has plenty of tables ready to play on in the afternoons.

Out and about with my son and he was craving pizza. Yelped and this was the closest pizza spot. So glad we stopped here. I ordered the two slice special and the pizza was amazingly good. The cheese and sauce on this pizza has a unique taste that amazed me the moment I bit in. And the bread, the bread is they type that makes that nice crunch sound when you bite in or squeeze. I normally like my bread and crust soft but this was so good. The service is excellent and the environment is great as well. Definitely worth a try.

Tired of the generic strip-mall corporate chain haircuts? Here's the solution. I've been going to BJ's for about 3 years and have never been happier with a haircut. Great place. Don't let the location fool you, its really nice inside.

Pool table and couch while you wait, great people, free shampoo after your haircut, it doesn't get any better. This is the hair-cutting equivalent of Cheers. "Where everybody knows your name...." And of course I can't forget to mention Mari, who I highly recommend you ask for.

Service was very good. Food was served quickly and was very good. I ordered the Americano which included amazing potatoes but in the eggs, there was egg shell which was very disappointing. It is also cash only, but there is a atm in the front.

It's nice to live in a small community like Catalina--it's great to support the local small-business owners--but one major drawback is that when an establishment is poor, you're sort of stuck with it unless you want to make a bona fide road trip. This particular store consistently runs a substandard operation--from the seemingly high-turnover staff to the poorly prepared food (freshness is always in question).

I have loved Arby's food all my life. I have lived in Catalina for just over 2 years. My takeout experiences here are generally horrible. I could just stop eating there...but like I've already said, I love Arby's and I have a right to good service. Other Arby's stores in town provide a good eating experience; why can't this one? The owner of this store should be practicing the same level of customer service and quality.

Now, on to tonight's experience...first off, I have since stopped ordering through drive-thru because their error rate for me is well over 75%; these days, I just go into the store for take out so I can ensure my order is correct right there on premises. My wife doesn't grab us takeout often, but tonight she did and they got her order wrong (big shock), they didn't know the special they were running (2-for-$5 fish sandwiches) and the food brought home (a 5 minute drive, mind you) was practically inedible; my fish tasted like it had sat under the heat lamp for an hour.

To "Mr./Mrs. Owner of this Store," you really have some problems, and frankly I'd love to hear your alibi.
Food was good ! Employees was nice . Laid back and chill . My Hubby , Son , and I had a great time . It was very quite . Just a few people . Overall , we were pleased !

I ordered black coffee. And I wasn't disappointed. From some of these reviews, it sounds like I should experience something heavenly when I sip. Nope. Just coffee. It was crowded and the baristas were ok. I don't expect a lot from a 20 second exchange. "coffee...with room" is all that is needed to be uttered. It was better than starbucks (whose coffee I hate). Truth be told, I kept coming here because it was a block away from the Rittenhouse which made it super convenient.

Atmosphere is usually pretty good, but service wasn't so hot today.  Once we placed our order, we were pretty much forgotten from that point on - except to drop off the check.  After five minutes, the server came back and asked if there was anything in the "book" (cash, card) and when we said "not yet", she seemed irritated.  We then asked for refills, the only time we had one, since she hadn't come back to check on us at all, that seemed to surprise her actually!  Someone else bright the refills.  The food was good, as it always has been, but the service was really liking this time around.

This new restaurant is so great. I went to get a carry out order and the service was great. They were so helpful and timely. The food was honestly some of the best Chinese food I have ever had. I got crab rangoon and fancy dragon roll. So so so good. Highly recommend.

Do not let the outside scare you away!  This locally owned and operated restaurant is full of flavor!! The wings appetizer was amazing and perfectly cooked.  The jerk chicken entree was amazing and authentic, just like my husband and I remembered from our trips to Jamaica.  The oxtail entree was so full of flavor, rich and delicious sauce that you could tell was cooked for hours.  The only complaint was the small bones you had to eat around.  The only reason this is not getting a 5 star review was the lack of atmosphere inside the restaurant.  The room get too big and lifeless.  The server was super polite but slow especially when you saw friends hanging out and chatting and a lot of the food items were precooked/slow cooked.  It is a place we would probably just get take out from in the future. It would definitely eat again!!

Ok, first I have to say that I'm a sushi/sashimi afficianado, so I'm very picky about my fish being fresh. I've been to some places througout the SF Bay area who "claim" to be sushi restaurants, who serve plain crap that a true sushi chef from Japan wouldn't dare serve.  

Granted that Reno is in the middle of the desert so I wasn't expecting the fish to be freshly plucked from the ocean, plus it was for an all you can eat special, so I knew the bulk of the stuff had to be frozen. I came in with the preconcieved notion that it wasn't going to be that good. I was pleasantly surprised. 

We opted for the all you can eat sashimi for $33. We didn't bother with the all you can sushi, even if it was $10 cheaper. C'mon folks you're not here to fill yourself up with rice and maki-rolls! Go for the good stuff. And go for the good stuff we did - unagi, ikura, tobiko, hotate, tako, ika, hamachi, tai, maguro, ebi, amaebi. We skipped the cheap stuff and dove straight in for the high ticket items. I think the restaurant  may have broken even with us. They ran out of tako and ika, and I saw they were running low on amaebi.  It was actually pretty good, considering it used to be, flash frozen fish.

Our sushi chef was Angel. He was very attentive and kept asking us if we wanted anything more. Well, duh!
The brunch burger was so good!! The waitress helped me picked out the perfect lunch, I enjoyed my dining
This is a much needed addition to our community! The fish + meat selections are phenomenal. Great produce. Also, try out the hot bar for AMAZING plantains, pastor, and rice!
Best Pub in Tucson. Love this place. Great service/prices and so much space! I love playing pool here.

Incredible fresh pasta with very imaginative small plates, fresh focaccia that's to die for, superbly friendly service and an excellent bar - one of my new go-to restaurants. My only complaint is that it was a little loud, then again, I'm a little old. Order a lot of everything, be adventurous and ask the wait staff what they like, they seem to have good taste. Crudo was clean, salty and sour, the gnocchi tasted Asian inspired, definitely a chef having fun experimenting, and the pasta dishes were both amazing. It's a cool little spot that's part of a very solid family of restaurants - I'd like to see this one take liberties with pasta as often as the inspiration strikes. Well done.

Called  with  a question and from the  woman  who  answered  to the  technician they  were so  sweet, helpful and  professional.  The  technician gave information  that  worked  right  away.  I will  be  using  this  place  for my  car needs  gladly.

Got here at like 1:15 ish on a Saturday afternoon and they were still serving brunch. It was the perfect spot for a friend I hadn't seen in a long time. If you have like a $60 budget for two people (entree + mimosa) I'd highly recommend this place. He loves his food and so did I! I got the chicken and waffles and a crab corn fritter appetizer. Super good. Will definitely return!

Purchased my 2016 RRS here and have always been very pleased with both the purchase process and now the service.  Just replaced the tires with all season Pirelli's and with the final balancing and adjustments, I was out in a few hours and it drives better than ever.  Everyone there is friendly and knowledgeable... this is a first class dealership.
Amazing yogurt! Awesome service! Highly appreciate the amount of sample cups provided ;)

We messed up our reservation and the manager was kind enough to help us to sort it out.  We asked for a pack and play and it was set up in our room ready to go.  Room is good and clean with microwave and fridge which is great for baby.  All in all a great experience for our stay in the burbs.

Bodega is my favorite place for a good Cuban sandwich. I literally crave it at times! It is that remarkable. So naturally when I was researching some other places to try, I just went for what I know. And I'm very glad I did. So my guy and I split the Cuban and the Frita burger. I highly recommend the Frita if you want to try something you won't on the menu find anywhere else. The Frita is Cuban style beef & pork with avocado, spicy mayo and potato chips. Lots of potato chips! Not that adventurous, stick with the Cuban. It was voted Best of the Bay for a reason!

Agave is definitely a unique Nashville establishment and is actually pretty cool if you can get over the people that frequent it.  It's a tequila bar, and as such has an amazing varieties of tequila to choose from, more than anyone in town.  The wall behind the bar goes from floor to ceiling housing tequila varieties of all kinds.  It's kinda cool watching the bartender climb a ladder to reach the type you've chosen to drink.  That being said it's confusing to me how when you go here, a tequila bar, the majority of the patrons are drinking bottles of Miller Light.  I mean don't you go to a tequila bar for tequila?  Some of their options can get pretty expensive as most high end tequila tends to be pretty pricey.

The place looks and sounds like a dance party more than a bar, and it tends to be the same group of people that hang out here every night.  They offer a limited menu, with a few appetizer type snacks.  The coolest thing they offer are tequila 'flights' and I highly recommend them.  You pick a different number of tequilas (the price varies depending on how many you choose)  and they're served in shot glasses which are situated in a piece of wood.  The flight comes with homemade lime-sicles which you use to taste the tequila.  Instead of just drinking the shots, you dip your lime-sicle into the tequila and drink it that way.  Its a great way to really taste the different flavors of the tequila, plus its just a unique gimmick.  This is definitely a bar and not a place to go for dinner.  If you like tequila, or just want a different kind of bar to go to give this place a try.  It's more on the dressy side, and seating is limited so either come early or be prepared to stand.

The Cracker Barrell is the Disneyland of the "chain restaurant": it seems to leave in a Southeast fairy tale.  I like the atmosphere and this sensation of home sweet home. The food is nice, and while you are waiting you can always browsing around in the store.

Went to a bachelorette party here and was very nervous. I am not artistic by any means, and I think the last time I picked up a paint brush was for a grade in high school. 

Our resident artist was just fabulous. He instructed us with both humor and constructive criticism. I'm actually surprised at how decent my painting looks, and I ended up having a great evening. I'm even considering taking my mom there for mothers day.

Best tattoo shop in philly and one of the best I've ever gone to. Very professional and great artists. Not pretentious. I've gotten several from Scott Bakoss and all of them have turned out great. I plan on getting many more at this spot.

This is an excellent place for fast, cheap, and delicious noodles. I've been here twice, but am sure to come back once I move down south. 

Their menu has a variety of different styles of noodle and rice dishes, with handy explanations of the features of each in the margins of each page. Good thing, because I don't know what "broken rice" is without it!

Both times I came here I had vermicelli rice noodles with prawns that comes with an egg roll. I can't remember exactly what the category was called, but it came with a sauce to pour over the bowl of noodles, veggies, etc. Really good for only about $7 a bowl, and it will fill you up. I can't wait to try more here!

The service is extremely fast, but don't expect any conversation or even a hello from the staff. I don't mind at all, somebody might. An apparent regular cam in while we were there, and was greeted with only "Same thing?" Haha!

Two of us came in at about 11:30 on a Thursday, and we were the only ones in there so food came in about 5 minutes. By 12:15 it was packed though! It's delicious!

What do we have here? Pottstown's finest.
I called for carryout. Asked for the tuesday deal named "Papas Play". The deal is valid tuesdays only and only if Monday night football total score adds up to 51 points..which it did. The girl who answered had not been trained in telephone ettiquite. Rude and yelling to a manager or another associate if they had heard of the deal. Both employees had no idea what I was talking about and she said "no we don't do that. Bye"
Click. Hung up. No suggesting another deal, no "can I get you anything else" just bye, click. So we spent 35 bucks at wawa.

I visited this restaurant when the hotel first opened over the Summer and was extremely impressed. I loved that they kept the original historic windows and decor as it is located in Historic Ybor City. You can find street parking across the street for a price, use hotel valet, garage parking or just find free street parking. Also, for out of towners beware that during events like Gasparilla there is just a flat rate for parking (excluding free street parking & valet). The hotel is located right near the main garage for 7th ave. The restaurant is on the 1st level, open space, a place for live music, there is also a cafe off to the right when you enter. 

The restaurant is pretty much the standard hotel restaurant space, but they have a small atrium which overlooks the pool and it lets in a lot of nice natural light. The first time we visited was when they first opened and service was 5 stars. Our waiter was friendly, attentive, and checked everything to see what was gluten free (I am a Celiac). My top recommendation is the ceviche, to be specific the le Tigre ceviche, its amazing! I have had it at other restaurants and this is the best I have ever had. The Chef's sausage trio would be next, 2 out three of the sausages are gluten free. Next, the Painkiller is a must have, the drink comes in an elaborate carafe shaped like a bird and its quite delicious. 

So, our next visit was not the same level of excitement, experience, or service. Our waitress messed up our order and somehow thought it made sense to blame me so my entree came out first and my starter came out with my husbands entree. I lost my appetite because after I asked for them to bring the salad like I originally asked they still brought it out with my husbands steak about half an hour later. She basically said I wasn't being clear about what I wanted and was like "whatever it isn't my fault". We had two completely different experiences months apart!
