It sucks because I ordered the steamed mussels and they tasted amazing when they were hot, but it basically sat on the table and got cold while I was waiting for the salad I originally ordered!!!!! I boxed up my salad to go because they brought it out at the end of dinner and it was soggy by the time I got home. I don't understand why she didn't just have them bring the items out as I ordered them once it became clear my entree came out as an appetizer.

 Overall, the food is five stars, although the menu is small they have some very nice options especially for Celiacs and I did not get sick eating here the items they said were gluten free were gluten free (I basically stuck to seafood and salad.. The live music was also great the time we visited and it was going on. We had a reservation both times and were seated promptly. There always seems to be a lot of people checking in, but now the restaurant doesn't seem to be aaas busy as during the Summer so any night is a good night to visit.

This is my second visit. Quite frankly, I can make it better at home. Tri tip was dry and overcooked. Chicken was tender but tasteless. Ribs were smothered in bbq sauce, tender but bland.
I'm glad the company paid. I certainly wouldn't go there if I had to pay.
Service was good. Ambiance is nice. 
Food is very average.

Nice Cuban style cuisine... the flavor is there!

The sandwiches are large so you can definitely share. The Cuban sandwich has good flavor but was a little dry (not a problem though, just get some mustard/mayo sauce). The pollo asado and the lechon are good too - lechon is my favorite. 

The "platos" (plates) come with black beans and rice, garnished with cilantro and a pickled spicy pepper. 

They have a few side dishes - the sweet & spicy slaw is good (not too mayonnaise-y). 

The only thing I found not too great was the hibiscus soda - only because they make it to order and don't shake it up real well.

Super clean and new. 
Our waitress was super nice. 
The kitchen messed up my order but they were more than accommodating. Let me keep the wrong sandwich (Buffalo chicken) to take home. 
My chicken parm was really good and messy, as expected. Good flavor and lots of cheese. 
Husband had the buffalo chicken pizza, hence where the booboo was made with my sandwich. 
Hubby really enjoyed his pizza. A small is 10 inches and perfectly done toppings. Very well spread out and he said it had really good flavor. 
We did both have the dinner salad. The salad is okay. Basic chopped lettuce with a cherry tomato, two black olives, two green olives, and a slice of cucumber. It's $2 to substitute the salad for the chips, she brought the chips anyway and they are plain ruffle type chips. The salad was okay nothing to write home about. 
When we got the check the manager took the salads off the bill due to the error. I really did not expect that, however very much appreciated. 
Looks like they have their customer service skills in check and their food is pretty good. 
We will be back for sure.
Awesome crispy chicken not overly breaded with good seasoning. The sides are good but was disappointed with the gravy fries. The wings were really good too.

Caffeine is awesome! Truly a craft coffee shop. Emily was kind enough to donate some free coffee cards to an event I organized for the National Pediatric Cancer Foundation. Unfortunately, I couldn't enjoy coffee the day I popped in to pick up the donation...but came back a few days later and had a fabulous pour-over prepared by Connor. Connor was super friendly and knowledgeable about coffee...and my cup o' joe was fantastic. I wish I worked downtown so I could enjoy this place more often, but I will definitely stop in any time I'm in the area! Highly recommend.

Stopped at Tiger Lily 2 for dinner.  The food was fantastic!  2 appetizers really stood out as exceptional.  The spicy chicken korean bao buns and korean dumplings were amazing.  The main courses everyone had were equally as impressive.

Friendly staff, which is hard to find these days. I called ahead looking for a used item and the lady over the phone was kind and had someone look for the item to see if it was in stock. She did not seem annoyed with the call. Then when I came to the store someone helped me look for the item and then found a new one in a box and also helped me to get a better deal. Then when I went to the cash register, someone behind the desk smiled at me. I know this may seem normal to some but it is RARE to find more than one nice person in an establishment. Also, the place was clean and organized.
Outstanding local bar and owners.  Bartenders are awesome and it is always a blast, especially when live music is taking place.

The prices are high, but the food and the experience made it worth it completely. Our server Nicholas was amazing. He was very knowledgeable of the menu and gave candid feedback on different items. Definitely a spot to go if you want top notch steaks and 5 star service. 
In addition, the valet was complementary so you don't have to worry about finding a spot.
Fast, efficient service. Has more than bagels. Great place for quick meal or snack before flight.

We stopped here on our way back to the Philadelphia airport after reading many positive reviews online. We loved the atmosphere immediately walking in the door. We were immediately greeted by a friendly bartender and server which is always a positive. The menu offered many options and we read they were noted on the Food Network at some point. It's a great spot with a lot of history. I personally ordered the buffalo chicken quesadilla and my fiancé ordered their pulled pork sandwich, both were very good. They also offer a good deal for small children on their kid menu. Overall we enjoyed our experience here and would for sure stop here again if it fits in our traveling plans. I would like to try some of their famous wings next visit. Enjoy!

Good toys and friendly salespeople who offer to gift wrap things!

I really really really miss Mrs. Tiggywinkles, and wish it still existed so I could buy the kiddos in my life presents from the same store my grandmother bought my presents from, but this isn't half bad.
Second time here for a 60 minute massage. Had such a good massage for a great price.  Look forward to another visit. Calming environment.

This place is always busy, so we don't go often. The couple times we did we thoroughly enjoyed it. Shark bites are greasy & the quantity is very small, but I can't complain, they are still sooo good & it's not like you can get them easily. Food times are efficient & the staff is wonderful.

This is the worst dollar tree anywhere.  The store is half empty.  It's been half empty for 6 months. They haven't had drain cleaner for 3 months and their frozen section is empty.  I've spoken to the RM and DM and neither one seems to care. Go to the one in Moorestown instead. It's great.

I give ONE STAR for their lack of customer service if you have to call them..Forget it.

I give FIVE STARS for some of their employees who go out of their way to help you. 

 I recently had an issue with a gestapo sales associate removing a hanger from my bag as I was leaving the store, saying i was not allowed to keep it, when the cashier asked if I wanted the hanger and put it in my bag at the register upon checking out.  After calling customer service 4 times the next day and getting disconnected, I went back to the store to get my hanger back (it was part of a gift for the clothing that I bought).  The cashier manager, Rob, understood the situation and provided me with outstanding service in making things right.  I left with my hanger and renewed faith in customer service at Sears.  I wish more people were like Rob, believing the paying customer and not treating them like criminals.

If you want junk beer, go anywhere, prices will be the same.  If you want good craft beer at decent prices, come here. I live in Horsham and drive past 2 distributers to get here.  most distributers have signs in windows saying "craft beer here" and you go in to be pointed to sam adams, magic hat 9 and victory golden monkey.  Hatboro has WIDE variety of craft beer

very nice property, great restaurant. we were very disappointed that the "dog" friendly room carpet is soiled so badly, it needs to be replaced. dog rooms shouldn't look like this, especially when we pay for the dog to be here.

Let's start off with the "special thank you email I received. Even a first grader could figure out they were supposed to fill in the blanks. [DealCreatedDate] and [VehicleDesription] and so on. Then we get to the review for my experiences.


Thank you so much for visiting Cycle Springs Powersports on [DealCreatedDate]. I really enjoyed meeting you and helping you with your purchase of the [VehicleDescription]. It is important to make sure that you are getting the quality and service you deserve with all of your important purchases. At Cycle Springs Powersports, we are dedicated to meeting all of our customers needs. Thank you for giving us the pleasure to meet yours. Our greatest compliment is a referral from a customer like you. Please feel free to contact me, [SalespersonName] at Cycle Springs Powersports at 727-771-1211 if you have any further questions about , or if I can be of any further assistance to you. Again, thank you for your purchase. I look forward to helping you with your future needs.

Sincerely, [SalespersonName] Cycle Springs Powersports

---------------------------------------------------------


Now the review for Cycle Springs Powersports.


Well this is a 50/50 review. I bought two bikes and both were "good deals" but just the lies that was told really sealed the deal and made me realize what a mistake I made dealing with this company. 

First review is for my Spyder. Things went so smooth and I didn't feel deceived till the helmet I ordered was to small and the parts guy said well to exchange you will have to pay the difference (which the helmets had same price) I was like they are the same cost. He was thinking they would return it as what they paid then charge me msrp for the new one. What twisted thinking they had. Then on the second bike they told me parts and accessories "at cost" I made a list of things I wanted (around $530) and he said I can save you $90. Part of this cost was to replace the pitted brake and clutch lever that can with the "brand new bike". I said that's not much of a savings. Then it was no longer "at cost" now it turned into "employee cost". So you are telling me you make money off your employees for the parts that they order? Any way, then my wife is supposed to be tax exempt and they said they would honor that and then the next day after he realized I had a problem with the "at cost" he changed the deal to where they couldn't make it tax exempt. Then I was to be added to the registration and once again they couldn't figure that out either. We did not recieve the owners manual for the bike. They had some kind of story that they could not give us a warranty nor the owners manual because they bought the bike from another dealer. Makes me wonder what else did I not recieve that I was supposed to get with the "new bike". I guess they think we should be happy with 2 keys. The owner called me and said he wanted to cancel the deal after my wife had already made a decision and deposit. Just a word to the wise if it's set in stone on ink take it and make the most of it but if not RUN FAST. I was also told gas is just under 1/4 cause if we put any more we would have to charge you more for the bike. You can tell it's money over customer satisfaction cause that was a douche move. I have added pictures of the levers taken day of delivery to show how much they really "care" that you get a quality bike and a fair deal.
Really good service very nice staff a little pricey overall great experience. I'm pleased. Nails help up pretty good.

The owners are very nice people however, you get what you pay for. Their prices are cheap because the quality is cheap. I would get a full set all the time and my nails would easily fall off from literally nothing... One day I asked from them to do my eyebrows and they guy replied "you're too tired maybe come back when you aren't so tired" really? That's how you talk to your paying customers?!

I think that I may be generous with my second star. The meal started out fine with a bowl of tomato-fennel soup which I found very tasty. Then things went downhill fast. My wife and I both ordered the double 5oz burger which we asked for as rare as they would make them. Both burgers came out well done- and the meat may as well have been from Burger King. I think that I would have enjoyed a Whopper more than this burger. When presented the bill, we showed our waitress the Groupon which we had downloaded. She had no idea how to deal with it. After 10 minutes of trying to figure out how to discount our meal with the Groupon, we were told that no one knew how to use it, the owner was away and he's the only one who knew, and then we were told that they only accepted Groupons for lunch- all of which sounded like BS. So we paid full price- never to go back. Oh, and if you're sensitive to mold, stay away. You can still smell the faint odor of mold remaining from pre-construction, thus the use of fans in the dining area.

Probably one of my favorite bar experiences in New Orleans thus far. 

Since it's located in a somewhat dodgy area of the French Quarter (the next block up is the projects) coming here at night seemed a bit scary, so we came here during the day around 2pm for a few cocktails. Bonus: their happy hour also runs from noon to 8pm. Daily $5 drink specials from noon to 5 every day is an extra bonus!

Our bartender Adrian was super friendly and helpful. I originally asked for a Ramos Gin Fizz, but she was out of eggs at the time, so I went with the 'Tru Kick': Tru Organic Gin, house made ginger syrup, lemon juice, lime juice & Fee. Bros. Peach Bitters. Delicious and refreshing.

Just as we were about to close our tab, the eggs arrived! Adrian graciously offered to make me one to go, as I had mentioned how much I wanted to try one given that it's a "New Orleans Original". Only in New Orleans can you get a perfectly frothy Ramos Gin Fizz to go. I love this city! And this bar! Definitely coming back to try more of their cocktail menu the next time I'm in town.

I usually don't leave Yelp reviews because I feel like you really have had to have the worst experience of your life to go out of your way... but here we are.

I went to Valère spa yesterday to get a brazilian wax while visiting Boise, I had actually been here once before for a massage a year ago but hadn't put two and two together (the massage was underwhelming to say the least). There's only one woman here that does the waxing, I believe her name is Brittany -- I'm sorry Brittany to be throwing you under the bust like this -- but it was by far the worst waxing experience I have ever had. Already a super unpleasant task to have to do, but this was another level of pain. I told her the wax was too hot, she didn't change the temperature, I continued to wince at the heat and she said "I think you're psyching yourself out". K. 

I left, didn't think much of it other than I won't be returning.

This morning I woke up to black and blue bruises and burns all over the area. Not even like a casual bruising because I was tensing my muscles, but full on black, terrifying bruise.

It's unacceptable for this establishment to think this is okay, and I hope they re-evaluate before they move forward giving any further waxes. Valére has you sign a waver before you get waxed basically saying reactions to the waxing process aren't they're fault, however I believe physical bruising and burning very much is.

We had our wedding at Elings and it was absolutely wonderful.  We had the ceremony in the ampitheater and the reception on the Godric's Grove deck.  We received so many compliments - everyone wanted to know how we found the place.  The park staff were very easy to work with throughout the process.  Our only complaint was that the outdoor lights didn't come on once it got dark so the bathrooms were pitch black for our guests.  Luckily we gave out flashlights as favors.  Even with dark bathrooms, we'd do it all again.

I had to book 2 buses for a work event and had a great experience working with Lynsey. She was super responsive and flexible throughout the booking process -even though I had some last-minute changes and a ton of questions. The coaches arrived early, they were clean and the drivers Bill & John were personable and professional.

Delicious! This place is definitely my favorite pizza place in levittown. Whenever I order for a group they always ask where I ordered from because it's so good. I can't say much about the rest of the menu because I never want to miss out on the pizza!

I've had the opportunity to go to this arena for multiple events (Sixers games, concerts, Disney on Ice, etc.). The Wells Fargo Center is beginning to show its age. The seats need to be updated as they are starting to deteriorate. The design of the Center is so vertical. If you're sitting in the 200 level, it feels like you might as well be sitting on the roof. If you've never been here and plan on attending for a game or a concert, shell out a few more bucks to sit in the 100 level, unless you're the type who does not mind nosebleeds.

The food selection is not bad, but the price is ridiculous. Then again, I can't think of any stadium that doesn't have ridiculous concession prices. It's usually hard for me to resist Chickie's and Pete's crab fries. If you can sneak in your own snacks, which I've done a few times, I would recommend doing so. I know it sounds tacky, but hey, a man's gotta do what a man's gotta do.

The service is always so quick whether we order ahead through the mobile app or we just show up and get in line at the drive-through! They are very efficient, the food is always fresh, and they haven't made a mistake yet on any of our orders. Even in the cold they all seem very genuine and kind. Keep it up!

I've been looking for a nail salon since I moved to the Philly area seven months ago. After seven months of bad mani-pedis, I found this place on my birthday was so happy. It's super cute inside, everyone is nice, and my nails are perfect. Totally recommend.

Have been using yellow cab for many years with only minor problems, but on 1-19-17 I called for pick-up at dental ofc that yellow had dropped me at a few hours earlier, and had dropped off and picked up 3 times in previous 16 months. Called at 8pm , told 20 min and driver would call. Called back at 8:30, dispatch told nurse I was no show, nurse told them no cab showed, front of bldg all glass so all front desk staff could see street, along with me at door. Dispatch said I was priority, cab there in 15 min with call from driver. 8:45 nurse called again, dispatch said driver came, called ofc number again, I was no show , so he left. Once again nurse said front of bldg all glass, etc etc, and dispatch said I was priority etc etc.9:10 pm, nurse called, said same thing, dispatch repeated lie from driver. By now, pain meds worn off, and pharmacy closed. Dispatch said same thing. Cab finally called at 9:30 and said 6 min out. When cab showed up, gal driving had no idea I was med priority, she just thought regular run. I was really surprised at the way she cut off other drivers! I hope the yellow cab company loses biz after I share this with my American Legion and Moose brothers.

So happy that I didn't have to look too much to find a good Thai restaurant. They make the food when you order, and it's not just sitting. The place is clean, and the staff is friendly, and they do explain the options to you. They have Thai tea also, so that made it even better. I never order anything other than the Pad Thai regardless of what Thai spot I go to . It's right across the street from where I work, so it's not far, and I can walk there and be in and out without rushing.
Our pastrami sandwich and caesar salad hit the spot for lunch the other day. The portions were generous enough to share between us. Very sweet to have a neighborhood deli!
Pizza could have been cooked longer...kinda chewy...I love that it's a drive up window.

The service and food are always good here. I've been here a few times and this sushi they offer is fresh, reasonably priced and good portions. The Thai food they offer is also very good and reasonable. The service is always top notch and very attentive. Compared to other sushi restaurants in the area this is my favorite. I'll keep coming back.

1.  First, the indicators are all good.  There's a wood pile outback, and the meat is served without any sauces whatsoever, both indicators of a restaurant that takes BBQ seriously.
2. There are six sauces on the table.  I thought two were way too sweet, but there were others I liked.  Pick your own.
3. THESE ARE THE WORST FRIGGIN GREEN BEANS EVER.  Seriously people, they tasted like they belonged in some vegan place.  Cook them 7 times as long and throw in some onion and pork fat.  I assume you've got pork fat?
4. Service was good.
5. Highly recommended, except for the green beans.

Súper good service, excellent cachapas with Venezuelan cheese (de mano y llanero). The passion fruit juice and tequeños were also amazing. Sooo much cheese on those tequeños. Honestly the best is the service! People who care! I saw it by accident going to Wesley chapel mall and my boyfriend stopped even though we were looking for salads. I am glad we went! Try it!
Ordered the soft shell and catfish bo boy.  Both were good.  And you know what else was good?  The sweet potato fries!

The jobs they post online are better than what they can offer you (seems like they are trying to fool people to sign up with them). Even if you call them about an opportunity you saw posted on the same day, they will say it's not available and offer something less desirable. Recruiters do not seem friendly or helpful. I felt that my interview was rushed; I wasn't even notified that the job I originally applied for was no longer available. I highly recommend trying a different agency.
This is the real thing.  Well worth a visit if your a fan of Mexican food.  The steak burrito is my favorite.  Nice people and good food make for around good meal.

As soon as I walk into this place I immediately feel like family. Everyone is so nice and genuine. Andy is a killer bartender who can put a smile on your face no matter what mood you're in! My new favorite local bar in Reno!

Retro looking motel very conveniently located close to the shopping streets and the funk zone. Borrow a bike and it takes 10 minutes down to the beach.

There's a mini mall close by and don't forget the coffee shop up the street Daily Grind. Awesome macadamia coffee and bagels.

The staff at Presidio were nice and room clean. The area was quiet and we slept well.

Ah, loved the sun deck too.

Between Judy's singing and Bobby Love's band, we had the best night of our short trip to New Orleans. Everyone was extremely fun and hospitable. They made sure we felt welcome, had plenty of beer, and danced as often as possible. Thanks Judy! We will be back!

This is the place to go with a large group.  If you want to eat like you are going to the electric chair then a Maggiano's trip is a must.  Our waitress Val was exceptional. A glass was never empty and our plates were gone as soon as we were finished with them.  Every year before Christmas me and about 15 guys I grew up playing hockey with come here for our "manfest".  We eat and drink like kings and are surprisingly comfortable for such a large group. Another perk to Maggiano's is the doggie bags, everyone seemed to get a huge portion in special containers with reheating instructions.  Gotta love that!

I decided long and hard about posting this but I had to do it. I was so disappointed with my food today. Now I haven't had The Fish House smoked mullet in over a year now and couldn't wait to go back and get it again. I order the smoked mullet and got the Grouper Sandwich with fries for my wife. Now granted, there was a crowd and there was a wait to get the food which I understand. I got the order to go but when I got home, the smoke mullet was cold to the touch like it had been in the fridge. I had to warm it in the oven, and when I started eating, I notice the scales were never removed. The only taste it had was smoke flavor, nothing else. I was pissed, I couldn't eat it and threw almost an entire half away. I filled up on my sides which was the cole slaw and fries. My wife's grouper sandwich had no flavor at all either, just dumped in batter and fried. This was nothing like the last time we had it. I don't know whose cooking but I think it's time to evaluate his skills.  Please do better

This location is an embarrassment to the Dooky Chase name. The beer is consistently horrible in that it's either stale or very close to stale. The menu hasn't been modified in years with any variants for frequent fliers and other regulars. The ONLY reason to visit this place is to enjoy some last minute time with friends before leaving from different gates. Management needs a major overhaul.

Rescued Furnishings opened about a month ago.  The brick and mortar store is adorably cute!  Upon walking in, you are likely overwhelmed with the enormity of the space.  There is handmade one-of-a-kind furniture and décor everywhere.  They had a wooden table at the front entrance, behind it there was a wooden fireplace/mantel, along the wall was another amazing table.  Each tabletop was covered with adorable home décor.  Handmade wooden cutting boards, snarky pillow cases, map with calligraphy lettering, table runners and place mats... everything a home décor enthusiast would want to spruce of the home to compete with those perfect blogger/Pinterest homes.  Perfect place to go when looking for a housewarming present or special on-of-a-kind home décor item for the person that has everything.

Their website has some items available for purchase
-metal sign that says "Faith" or "Fearless" for $40
-handmade cutting board ranging from $50 to $60
-map with calligraphy lettering $35
-pillows for about $15/each

Wanted a bite to eat before a concert! Had their version of a Manhattan cocktail! Was not impressed! Ordered chopped steak and red beans and rice, yes I know they're a pasta restaurant but didn't like selections!! The steak was burnt and very dry. The red beans and rice were extremely spicy but lacked depth of flavor! The rolls were great as was the salad with blue cheese! Was disappointed with food! The service was on point, though! I would suggest Spaghetti Factory instead if in the 2nd Ave. never disappointed there!

Two stars for overpriced, basic burgers.  Two stars for overpriced, small sodas.  Two stars for being directed to a kiosk to order and feeling like a burden when I declined.  

A BILLION STARS for the onion rings, which is the only item we will order here as takeaway so we can eat them with better food from someplace else. So the onion rings get the third star.  

Get ready for the customer service copy/paste response in 3... 2...  PS - I don't care if the burgers are Angus, never frozen, whatever.  They aren't special tasting and they're expensive.  I (and everyone else I know) just want decent food for a decent price.

First time visiting NoLa, came here for breakfast at about 9:30 on a Saturday with my brass band from Brooklyn. Atmosphere was great and we got seated immediately (great timing as we were a group of seven and there was room for us, got pretty crowded after we sat). The menu was hard to choose from, because everything looked so good! But I knew what I had to get, Chicken & Waffles! We all ordered up, it took about 30 minutes for everything to come out together which felt like just the right amount of time for fresh cooked food to be prepped during a morning rush. The food was 10/10. Chicken tenders were perfectly crispy but nice and juicy on the inside. The waffle was made out of sweet potato which I had never heard of before and tasted out of this world. It came with a bbq sauce on the side which almost tasted like a zesty ketchup but was REALLY good. That paired with some syrup and crystal (hot sauce) was everything I was looking for. On top of that, it was a decently large sized portion but felt very light to eat. 

Everyone else's food was 10/10 as well. Our waitress (didn't catch her name but she was a tall blonde with a pony tail and buzz fade on the sides) recommended we get coffee with... home made bailey's someone at the restaurant made. I got OJ but took a sip (and a whiff) of someone else's coffee. First off.. that smell though.. pure ecstasy. The taste, it was a real full-bodied subtle bailey's. 

Highly recommend this place.

Stopped by for lunch after visiting the nearby library- it's a very pleasant place where the diners all know and say hi to one another with great coffee, however the food was mediocre. I had a bacon egg and cheese sandwich that had a thin sheet of egg with a smoky aftertaste, which made me question how the egg was scrambled and if it was a real egg and not from powder. My bf got the roast beef special of which he could barely eat half. Bless his heart, he accepted our waitress's offer to pack the rest up to go, politely left with the container, and promptly tossed it in the trash can across the street.

Don't do it. 

I was stupid twice.

I have been here twice. Both times I ordered the M2 Package ($31 plus taxes). The second time I added the Floor Mat Cleaning for $10 additional. 

On my first visit here I ended up having to clean my windows, wheels, vacuum, and clean the bumper. Finally, they sent three guys over to help me work on my car. I ended up being the project manager. Nice.

First visit, $34 plus change, 45 minute wait 20 minutes of my own labor. Clean car.

On my second visit here I had to clean the wheels, the wheel-wells, and windshield. They did not even pretend to wipe down the dash, console, or clean interior of the windshield. They told me my car was ready and my floor mats were not even installed. This is a bad deal for $44 plus change. 

Second visit, $44 plus change, 50 minute wait, and 15 minutes of my own labor, and then returned for 20 minutes for cleaning and talk with owner. Very frustrating for an hour an half and $44. Even after showing the owner popcorn in my car, it's still in the car with me.

One of the managers explained to me that Saturdays are staffed with temp workers. He said if I really want to clean car, come during the week when the staff are true employees.

Well, I'm $80 in. I was stupid twice. I won't stupid again. But at least I have popcorn to munch on!

DONT GO!!!!!!!! 
This place is a scam!!!!!!
The nails are disgusting and their attitude is even worse!!!!!!!
Don't ever go!!!!!!!!
Great atmosphere. You will feel that you are eating in a Mexican place in LA. The burrito was good. I liked the service a lot.

This place has the worst service. The bartenders straight up ignore you. Me and my friend waited 10minutes at one bar and then decided to go inside so maybe we wouldn't be ignored in there. Nope. Another 10 minutes for 2 margaritas. We got there around 10pm and the closing time said 10pm online so we asked a female bartender and she LIED and said they closed at 11pm when they closed at 12am.  So then we moved to a table and our order was messed up twice and we had one more drink and left.

Some cool and interesting options, nice employees too, sometimes the food can be lacking and unfortunately even bland. I dont think they get enough customers here. The food has gone significantly downhill since opening. Here's to hoping they can get better again, used to love this place.

We consistently have a great dinner, or lunch, here. Recently, Sabrina, our server made our evening especially great. We had a 2 year old with us and she was amazing! She took her time with us, was patient, suggested some things for us from the menu, and engaged with our little one like no server has before! It was a really great dinner and experience. Our family will keep going back here because they consistently have really good food and service.

Traveling around the St. Louis and Mississippi River area this was a nice, super-casual place to have breakfast before a day of sight seeing.  We ordered omelettes and they were big, fluffy, and fantastic.  The hash browns weren't as browned as I prefer, but still good.  Some very reasonably priced entrees are available although I felt the a la carte menu was overpriced for a restaurant of this type.  Bright clean and large dining room with friendly servers. While I was not in the mood for a "sweet" breakfast they have a mouth watering array of delicious stuff on their menu like fruit crepes and flavored pancakes, French toast, etc.  Check it out especially if you like breakfast food!
Delicious food. Great Ambiance. Awesome Service. Make sure to order the Bruschetta Tostones and tres leches cake, you won't regret it.

Your average Chinese buffet, not amazing, nothing terrible. For less than$15 you have access to all your Americanized Chinese food, plus some prime rib, sushi, snow crab legs, and crawfish. But they are purposefully slow at refilling the more expensive items like crab legs and crawfish. Sushi quality looks questionable, so I didn't really eat it. All in all, this place did the job of being your cheap Chinese buffet. Probably will knock out after your meal though from that MSG overload... we ended up sleeping at 8:30 that night!

We have been really looking forward to getting back to Marsh House (one of our go-to local neighborhood places, pre-COVID) to see if they could hit the ground running at the high level of quality they were at many months ago with a new chef, new main entrance directly to the street (rather than through the Thompson Hotel lobby) and some cosmetic changes. The answer is, YES! Had an overall wonderful meal on a nice Friday night. Service was knowledgeable and efficient. The bartender knows how to make a great Black Manhattan. Autumn Salad was excellent; shrimp toast was the best I have had. Scallops and black squid ink  bucatini was outstanding. Tennessee Whiskey ice cream dessert was very tasty and special. We will be regulars again!

I'm not sure how or why this is separate from the "Pat O'Brien's" entry as they seem to be one in the same.

This place is all about the hurricanes. They were not as delicious as I remember. In fact, they tasted bitter.  The deep red color made me think there was a lot of syrup mix, but there was no sweetness.  Perhaps I've gotten used to the recipe I use at home, which features more fresh ingredients.  Either way, I was disappointed.

The patio seating is great to just hang out and take in the scene. They have outdoor heaters so you should be comfortable in any season as long as it doesn't rain.

As several have mentioned, take your glass back to the bar if you want a $3 refund.  If you can get it home without breaking, a $3 souvenir from this classic Bourbon Street stop is a pretty good deal.

Out today and had to kill a couple of hours. Had a gift card for Olive Garden so stopped in for dinner. Sat for a while and got our drinks. A little extended time but not bad. Ordered apps and dinner. A couple that sat down after us was served salads and apps before us. We even had the same server. Oh well. Got our salad and then the apps showed up. Part of it was missing but they quickly fixed it. While waiting for our dinners, I watched the buss guy come over to clean a table. He had his buss tray almost full. He set it down on a chair and pulled some menus out of the buss tray with the dirty dishes. He never cleaned them. He walked over and placed them in the rack on the wall with the other menus. That seemed nasty but looks like that was standard practice. Got our food. My dish seemed to be extremely salty but I thought it was just me. My wife tried it and said that it was. Overall the service was not too bad but the atmosphere after seeing the dirty menus and salty food I just seemed to find more faults. Don't think I will be returning.

This place is the reason fast food workers won't get $15 an hour. I just got off. Went to 2 other fast food locations, this was my last one. The workers are flirting with guys outside the front and had them park their cars in the drive through lanes so customers couldn't order. It's sad, disappointing, and frustrating. If you don't want to work, don't apply for the job. You are earning free money by not having to work at all. It's ridiculous.

Came here for lunch on the last afternoon of our vacation. We thoroughly enjoyed the salad, paninis, and pizza. Our server, Chris, did a wonderful job of helping us feel welcomed and comfortable. Service was quick and friendly. Sit out back if you can, the view is very nice!

Some of the best pizza I've had in a long time, the best in Delco. Pizza crust is out of this world, delish even when cold and toppings are made from quality ingredients.  I've tried the Snap dragon (which is my fav), the Ivory, Monte Carlo, and southern Bell, all very well thought out in terms of flavor profiles. The staff is friendly and passionate about their products. I would def recommend this place to anyone looking for great quality pizza.

CCS is the worst medical supplier I have ever dealt with. i have been diabetic for over 30 years and never had the problems I have had with them. They bill my insurance company and do not send the supplies. I have been hospitalized because of this and plan further recourse. They lie and just want money. They care nothing about the patient. 
DO NOT TRUST CCS ESPECIALLY IF YOUR LIFE DEPENDS UPON IT!!!!!!

Got an email this morning from their mailing list. I thought it was just another regular ad for their catering or something and was surprised to see it was a offer for a free sandwich for my birthday.

I was looking forward to my sandwich all day and walked about 20 blocks round-trip out of my way to go get my dinner. When I told the girl behind the counter I had a coupon and showed her the email, she said "I don't think we accept those anymore." I told her that it had been sent out this morning so unless policy changed mid-day it should still be good. She called a manager on the phone and then hung up and told me the coupons were from "the old ownership" and they weren't accepting them. 

And that was it. She didn't try to offer a drink or an order of fries or anything. Very disappointing. I will be taking my money elsewhere to get dinner.

Alright. Out of all gyros in Tucson, this is the place to go. Big, stuffed gyros with huge ass fries. Good stuff for Tucson.

But here's my complaint. Chicken Soulvaki*. It's the most expensive cardboard I've ever eaten. I'm pretty sure all the chicken dishes in this restaurant blow. Seriously, the chicken breast strips were disgustingly dry, no amount of yogurt dressing could've saved it. AND I thought prices for cardboard boxes in UPS were bad!

Cool gyros. Disgusting bird. Cutie with a booty behind the counter also.

Very nice hotel and great price for the location! Located just a short walk from both shopping and funk zone. The staff was very nice and the room was comfortable. Will stay here again on my next visit

Great service, great quality.  The "best burrito" or "taco" or "___" is an ephemeral American question and Super Burrito serves me right every time.  The quality for the price is outstanding and it's a drive-thru or dine in establishment to boot!

Drive up and order a chicken taco on your way between where you are and where you have to be and you'll go out of your way to repeat the experience!  

Staff is always sweet ... I think their secret is that it's run by a bunch of ladies who work well together and have high standards.  

Also in a time and a town where some things have gone downhill, this place has stayed as good as it was when it satisfied my cravings 15 years ago.

Bravo!

Food/service and atmosphere is always great!! 

We had a guy named Gray a few weeks ago and Kelsey ( I think) , last night. Both rocked it!!

I have never had a bad meal there. The owner is a stickler- I worked for him for a minute, and he's new in this biz, but he's doing something right!!!

It's a go to place- always consistent.

This is a nice little Greek/Turkish place with a nice decor that's open until midnight on Sundays. 
I ordered the Kebab Lamb Sandwich, and it took longer than I expected to be completed. The sauce was rich, but the meat felt a little dry and a little charred. I also ordered some fries to go, which were richly seasoned and tasty. 
I'm interested in checking out their other menu choices.

Attended the Otaku South Extra Large at Marathon Music Works. Cool event, although wish they had bands instead of a dj. 
Chose the Otaku South Ramen which was labeled spicy with ground pork, sesame oil, and some other stuff. It was really good. My husband thought it wasn't spicy, but I thought it was just right. It was super flavorful, even though the noodles are what you expect ramen to be, but the depth of flavors were great. Wish there was a tad bit more meat in it, however, it was very filling. However, it is simple food, nothing fancy. Best part? I didn't have that sodium-laden, thirsty for water-all-night feeling I usually do after eating Asian food. It was the real deal and I'm excited to try another pop up event. Next time I want to try one with the egg. My dining neighbor had it and looked amaze. Yum Yum!!

We only came in because we were intrigued by the magical high five for our Yelp check in.
We did even get two :)
Tasting menu looked good, and the interior was really cute - even with an adorable attractive patio.
We will be back and update our review after tasting soon.

Prices are right, service is great, and it's so close to home in the cutest location. Came twice already and have not been disappointed at all. Parking can be rough certain times, but it's better than the city.

Linguini Al polpo di granghio - Crab in a tomato sauce. This was really good. Sauce tasted fresh and there was tons of crab meat all throughout. What could have made this dish slightly better is if they used jumbo lump crab meat. I was trying to dig some out of my kids and only got bits and pieces (although there was tons of the bits).

Tagliatelle al profumo di bosco - wild musrooms in a cream sauce. So, the menu said it was also supposed to have fresh diced tomatoes, but mine came with none. The dish was good, but felt very very heavy. Although the tomatoes wouldn't have made the dish feel lighter, it would have helped a lil bit. The mushrooms were delicious though! Loved that they put plenty in the dish.

Creme brulee cheesecake - SO GOOD! I loved the glazed sugar on top of cheese cake. The cake itself wasn't light like regular creme brulee, but it wasn't so heavy like a standard cheesecake. It was definitely a nice combination of both.

I will be back! :-)

I want to start out by saying that I would probably have given Tinto 4 stars, however I am writing this review in comparison to Jose Garces' other restaurants that I've been to. 
After eating at Amada and Villiage Whiskey (both tapas style) I have to say that Tinto was the least impressive of the three, though still highly regarded. 

We ordered several items, all of which were quite yummy (prawns, shortrib sandwich, artichokes, sausage, figs, and a few others). The food came out VERY quickly and before we knew it we had exhausted what we ordered. It didnt help that I hadnt eaten all day either. 

Basically, the food and drinks were very elegant and worth the price, however, the food is a different experience entirely from Chef Garces' other tapas places.

I went to Neyow's Creole Café for dinner last Friday and it was quite the opposite of the experience I'd enjoyed for lunch earlier this month.  I sincerely hope that it was merely a result of the restaurant being sparsely occupied during my earlier visit, as opposed to being jam packed on Friday evening.  The difference though was most probably due to my choice of menu items.  For my lunch visit I had a chef salad which included all fresh ingredients that required very little preparation.  For my Friday evening meal, I had grilled shrimp with side orders of parsley potatoes and carrot soufflé.  The Friday meal of course required cooking and it just wasn't prepared very well.

We ordered two bottled beers, 1/2 dozen of oysters on the 1/2 shell and 1/2 dozen of char-grilled oysters.  Both oyster options were great and we polished them off in no time flat.  However, due to the large number of patrons on hand, we waited quite a while for our entrées to arrive, so that by the time they finally arrived, I was not about to send mine's back to have it redone correctly.  Instead, I accepted a meager amount of shrimp in the middle of a large dinner platter, with some sort of dark brown sauce decoratively drizzled over the open spaces of the platter.  On one end of the platter was a scoop of carrot soufflé and on the other end of the platter was a serving spoon of parsley potatoes.  Worse yet, the grilled shrimp were overcooked with the tails still on, and I had to chew the shrimp out of the shells because I was not able to pull the overcooked shrimp out of the shells.

I would have fared much better had I ordered the smothered okra with fried chicken as did Ann, who had too much to eat.  I, on the other hand was still hungry when we departed.

This store is horrible just like it always has been for years! Had horrible experiences there 4 years ago. Thought I'd try again.  They will lie to your face as if it's no big deal. I was told by a customer service rep at this store that Verizon doesn't honor my corporate discount from my employer anymore. Guess what, they do after visiting another Verizon location and couldn't tell me why I would be told such a thing. They just needed to pull up my account to verify, linked to my cell number. So I went back to purchase an accessory screen cover. Just to try a different employee. They tell me that no discount is available on the pure.gear screen protector. So I went to another Verizon store, they asked my phone number and honored my 20% off discount through my employer. Never again.. 
Be a great place for a legitimate business!

Very Pleased!

Before we sat down they had a baby chair waiting for our little one. The waitress is friendly and attentive, she even asked if we needed a bottle filled for the baby ( that's a first after 6 kids and 19 years!!!). 

Spinach dip is very good. 

Chicken plate is excellent and so is the Thai salad. 

Ambiance reminds me of restaurants in Los Angeles in the 70s - subdued lighting, candles on the tables, soft music. Very nice and something I miss in dining out today.  

The manager runs a very good restaurant. The staff is polite, efficient and their appearance is impeccable. And as stated the food was excellent. All signs of a well run restaurant. 

We will be coming back.
The doughnuts are ok, but the last time I went one of the employees was chasing a rat out of the restaurant as I was walking in with my mother. Definitely the last time I go there.

The workout was good. Although I left a pair of nice earrings there. I called and was told they had them and would hold for me. My sister went in two and half weeks later to pick them up for me and they all of a sudden disappeared. She was told someone would call me to discuss this. No one called. So I called again. Talked to someone and was told someone would call me the next day. No call. I called again. Was told a managed or owner would call me the next day. Still no call. Owning a business is about costumer service which this place lacks immensely. Someone has my earrings or knows what happened to them. I will continue to call and write reviews til this is resolved.

Simply amazing!!!!
Spent time in Paris and this place is a great reminder of the wonderful food in Paris!!!

This is (unfortunately for my car) the second time I have used Service King, and I am genuinely grateful to have had another extremely positive experience with this company. As a single gal without much car savvy, it was a relief to have had Brent Durham and Jim ensure I was properly taken care of and got a boost in service from the rental car company that had given me some grief. This time around, I personally requested Service King to do my repairs rather than taking "any old" insurance suggestion. Thanks for being awesome, guys!

A-DDIC-TED!  I have never been a person who would just go somewhere and order a salad but this place is really as good as it gets.  Fairly long lines during lunch but they move sooooo quick that you can still get in and out in a decent amount of time.  They are super efficient.

I like trying a lot of the seasonal salads.  I've had the strawberry fields salad with shrimp which is a summer salad that originally had me hooked to this place.  I can't wait for summer to get it again.  I got it three times in one week.  

There's another seasonal salad called the fall house salad which has apples and cranberries.  I can't recall the name of the pear salad that I had recently but it was good also.  You can pick if you want light, medium or heavy dressing.

I highly recommend anything lol but enjoyed each of these:
BBQ chicken wrap
Taco truck wrap
Thai shrimp peanut wrap
Too many salads to even name

Don't forget the chocolate Oreo cookies at the register.....DELISH!

I love this place.  I feel like I need a punch card to get something off after the 10th salad because I've far exceeded that.  The salads are extremely filling and worth the price.  Always nice people.  I'm definitely a fan!

i'm only rating this based on buying crap, not selling, okay? it seems like a lot of the bad reviews are based on them not taking people's stuff, causing a lot of hurt feelings. 

you need to go in with two things in mind:
1. don't go in looking for something specific, because there's no guarantee you'll find it. go in and just fart around and you'll end up with cute stuff.
2. don't go in with like, 5 minutes to look around. you need to spend a little time picking through shit, so don't be impatient.

everyone that works here has always been super friendly to me. the store is clean and as well-organized as a used clothes/consignment place can be and they have a ton of stuff, including jewelry and other accessories. give it a shot!

Our BBQ Shrimp was stunning, and so was the Acharuli Khachapuri served with it.  A fascinating union of Georgian and Creole cuisine, and the Khanjluri dances the wait staff do while shooting Chartreuse is nothing short of transfixing.
The facility is beautiful and very relaxing and comfortable. My esthetician Frank was amazing! I will definitely be back!

My first stop on my shopping rounds... place seemed like it would be very nice on the weekends but maybe during the week they are tired or trying to recover from a busy weekend.  I walked around without anyone saying hello as all the ladies were engaged in a gaggle of their own and they seem to have a lovely time at the shop so that was nice to watch. Kind of an odds and ends type of shop. Good place to start a little walk around the area though.

My husband and I ate here last night for the first time. An awesome hidden gem of a place. We took ages choosing just because everything on the menu looked so great. The waiter was very attentive, helpful, and accommodating. The food was mostly absolutely amazing. The scallop starter was delicious... salad... lobster very tasty though a wee bit overcooked (our only complaint). My husband said the creme brulee was better than his own which is a supreme compliment! Even the coffee... amazing. The sugar stick in the cappuccino was a lovely flourish. This will be a favorite for date night and to take visitors. Food, drinks, decor, service, ambiance... all great.

Nine Ting is an AYCE hot pot and Korean bbq. My experience here was better than I expected and the service was remarkable. Our waiter, Kevin, was really nice and friendly. He even taught us how to cook the Korean bbq and at times he even cooked it for us. I'd say the soup base was average and the meat flavoring was average as well. But still good. Overall I enjoyed eating here. I would totally recommend people to come try it out.

I love diners and was excited to try this place.  The place was bright and the walls covered in mugshots... duh. Our waitress was in a bad mood for sure. She asked us what we wanted to drink angrily and we just kind of laughed it off.  She looked like she got dumped and then was called into work on her day off.  Our table was next to the counter, she leaned over the counter completely to put our drinks on our table and pushed them closer to us with little nudges from her finger tips. Um okay. She did the same with one of our dishes, we just grabbed it from her. 

Anyway, the food was pretty good. My boyfriend didn't like that the pancakes were made with corn, but I thought they were very good.  His sandwich was huge... I didn't taste it, but he sure enjoyed it. The order came with 5 and I barely ate 2.  They were huge and very fluffy, I was going to definitely take the remainder home.  One of my pancakes ended up not being fully cooked on the inside and an older lady who worked there was so furious that that had happened. I wasn't even mad...  She apologized and INSISTED I give the plate back so she could give me a new order.  I said it was alright cause I was full, but she wouldn't take no for an answer.  Another young gentleman, came over to apologize as well.  She complained to the cook, took it off my bill and packed me up 5 new yummy pancakes to "have for breakfast tomorrow."  Unnecessary, but still nice! (I enjoyed every single one of those for lunch, dinner and breakast the next day.)

I would give this place 3 stars, but didn't because sometimes people have bad days.  We were able to laugh it off, but a lot of customers wouldn't appreciate the service the waitress barely provided us with.  She may think it's just a diner, but still, don't bring your problems to work.

I have been seeing Dr Bloch for the past 8 years.  As a retired (disabled) nurse practioner I am pretty well versed in the medical world.  And as a person who has lived with MS for almost 30 years I am a good judge of neurologists.  And I think she is one of the best.  She listens, she spends as much time with me as I need, and most important she provides the highest quality care I have ever received.  I always recommend her to others if I'm asked.  I know many of her other patients through my MS support group and they share my high opinion of her.  If you live in N NV and have MS then you should become her patient.

Where do I even begin? My family and I arrived in New Orleans and our hotel wasn't ready to check in quite yet. We asked the bellman for a quick breakfast spot, and without hesitation he referred us to the Ruby Slipper. We were seated right away and our server, Melvin, greeted us with a warm and genuine New Orleans welcome! Everything was absolutely incredible from start to finish. I ordered the New Orleans iced coffee and I have NEVER had a better cup of coffee! I ordered the Croque Madame, and my mom ordered the Bacon Prailines Pancakes (I ate half and went back the next day and my entire family indulged in these, do yourself a favor and order a stack). Melvin was absolutely attentive from start to finish! He made us laugh, had everything in a timely manner, and anticipated our needs when it came to refills. I can not recommend the Ruby Slipper enough! My only regret is not buying a shirt (and not going there for our last day!)

Got this Yelp recommendation...glad I did!
Excellent food, great dining area, country music, cute staff, fast service.  What else do you want?

Since this person keeps asking me for an update. Here it is. I got what I needed. This was crap service and apparently has someone invested in the law firm that keeps messaging me. Leave me alone! My review was honest and real and how I felt. That's what this app is for, correct? Correct. My original review stands correct.
Most amazing lobster and shrimp tacos! Ordered online for Covid takeout. Quick and excellent service.

Tcb downtown is a highlight of my work life balance. I've been here so many times for happy hours post work I can't even begin to count. Most notably was my work friend happy hour for my birthday last year. I typically go to tcb roughly 1-2 times a month and here are some reasons why it's the greatest happy hour place in Tucson. 
1. You can make a large reservation and everyone on separate tabs. 
2. Happy hour prices are great. 1/2 price apps are my favorite! 
3. Great ac during summer. Other breweries are definitely too hot to frequent in summer temperatures. 
4. Bring your own cake or decorations for parties! They put my cake in the fridge while we ate. 

Lastly the wings are great. Boneless is my favorite and the Jamaican jerk with a side of hurricane is wonderful! Service can be slow sometimes so o dock a star. Frankly I would of liked to have two servers instead of one when I'm sitting at a table with 20+ people. Anyways it's great and I'll defiantly be back soon.
Great beer selection. Plenty of drafts to choose from.  Specials available on the menu. Fish tacos. Nachos and chicken avocado wrap are favorites.

Brunch smunch. I can't tell you the last time I ate breakfast here before 7pm, but it's always solid.  

Dinner specials change regularly and are always great.  Polenta fries and South west buffalo chicken Cobb salad may possibly my favorite meal.

As seafood maniacs, when my fiancé and I want a date night we know won't disappoint, we go to 801 Fish. We were in Friday night and wanted a variety so we stuck with small plates for the night with some of our favorites.

You can't go wrong with anything on the menu but our favorites include the tuna tartare, jumbo shrimp cocktail (they don't currently have crab cocktail due to supply issues), hush puppies and crab cake. We also got the calamari and mussels which are excellent as well. 

We always get the brussels sprouts - they roast them to perfection and smack them with salty umami flavor. The clam chowder was creamy heaven and my fiancé enjoyed his gumbo as well. 

Always get dessert at 801 - they had seasonal pumpkin cheesecake that was to die for!

801 Fish always serves up great drinks and some of the highest quality seafood in the city. The menu isn't crazy innovative, but they do the classics and they do them well.

I went here last night to get my acrylic nails soaked off in attempt to save my natural nail underneath. When I came in, the guy who sat me down insisted I should have them cut shorter or just filled in. I said no, I want them off. He did, however, convince me to to get my acrylics redone after, as I had been planning to eventually, and there was no wait. So we sit down to take off my nails and he starts prying them off. I told him that I usually gave them soaked off, he continued to pry them off. Even when I said he was hurting me. Even when he burned me. Even when I insisted on the soak. He said, oh, you want to soak them? I said yes, he continued to pry them. I sat there and took it. Awful. If I wanted to just rip them off, I would've just done it myself for free, and even a lot gentler, too. I didn't want to be manhandled and disrespected any further, so I told him I would not be getting my acrylics redone and to just charge me for the remove so I could leave and never EVER come back.

This is the only true noodle joint in Indy that I have found. This is not your typical hole in the wall asian cuisine. This is authenticate Vietnamese dining! Easily my favorite type of cuisine and one that this city drastically lacks when compared to others. Lucky or us, there is Saigon. From the traditional Pho to the cold vermicelli noodle bowl, Bun, you can't go wrong at Saigon!

Love this restaurant! 
Made reservations for my daughter birthday . 
The food was awesome had the lobster toast, steak frite, the shrimp tacos, our peach cocktail and chocolate /Cheesecake.
Our server was awesome! 
When I get great customer service I tip close to 30% and that's exactly what I did.
You can also sit outside surrounded by beautiful greenery and flowers.
I recommend this restaurant and I will return.

Sessano Cafe & Deli is a charming spot right off from Route 202 and Johnson Highway! It's an Italian cafe and deli. Their hours aren't the best (they're not bad, but they're not open late), so try to stop in when they are open. There's ample seating. If you get to meet the owner, say hi, he's a cheerful guy.

Much of their menu is made-in-house (try the homemade soup or poundcake). There are non-Italian choices on there, like breakfast choices or greasy appetizers (onion rings or fried mushrooms, anyone?). Don't get their cheeseburger (Black Angus) - while it has (awesome) french fries and a large pickle, the buns are large and dry. The patty itself is so-so. I felt adventurous, and paid for it.

Definitely try their Sessano special hoagie - it has prosciutto, salami, capicolla, provolone, fresh (!) mozzarella, tomatoes, roasted peppers, and basil. We think we saw olive oil in there too. It's as fresh as it sounds! Their large (12") is $12.95, while the regular is $6.95. Worth every bite. I've had it three times so far and LOVED it each time.

Our Airbnb was right next door so I had to check it out.  Disclaimer: this review is just for the record store, I didn't get a chance to eat here. But I think it's a great business plan to put a record store right next to a bar. have a few drinks before you go shopping and it's almost guaranteed you buy something. 

From what  I saw it was 80% new vinyl and then some used in the back area.  I found a Beastie Boys record that I had been searching for so I walked away happy.  They had a great selection of different genres.

Excellent! They don't have gluten free items marked on their menu, so we decided to stop in and ask in person with a backup restaurant in mind in case they couldn't accommodate. The hostess knew exactly what I was asking (sometimes I still get a blank stare, which is really surprising for the food industry this day & age) but couldn't point out exact dishes, so she promptly brought over someone who could (thank you!). Once seated our server was very thorough in checking with the kitchen on the ingredients in the sauces & seasonings (thank you!). We ordered the guacamole, which was served with corn chips, and I had these amazing swordfish kabobs over rice. My husband (not gluten free) had lobster and avocado quesadillas, which he said were fantastic. We also had a couple of margaritas. The service was very attentive throughout the meal and the decor is very well done - rustic Spanish chic from the light fixtures to the tile floors.

i am visiting tucson and wanted to get a mani/pedi at my usual place, but my friend insisted we come here! she said that the prices can't be beat, and that the quality is great. 

we had appointments for gel manicures and pedicures and the staff here at lovely nail are quick, courteous and efficient! 

they use quality products and give great massages. my friend raves about how well her polish lasts, and i am sure mine will last until i am back home.

this place is worth checking out if you're in the area, but also worth the drive.

I would give this zero stars if I could. EVERY single time I go here there is an issue. Whether it be waiting in the drive thru for 20 minutes, to after waiting 20 minutes my order coming out wrong. This is the most unorganized establishment I've ever been to. Not to mention unprofessional. One time they put my hash browns in the bag with no paper cover, literally just the hash browns. This McDonald's needs a whole new more professional staff. I get it's McDonald's but seriously, have some standards. I've never left a yelp review before but after multiple mishaps here, I've reached my breaking point.

I have been wanting to try this place for some time and finally had the chance to do so. I really like they have numerous vegetarian/vegan options on the menu. The atmosphere inside is a little bland, pretty basic and boring really, but clean and there are plenty of tables. It's not really clear when you arrive if you're supposed to order at the counter, or wait at a table to someone take your order. It appeared that other customers were doing both. Also there is a written menu on the wall at the counter, and also a paper table menu that appeared to have different items, so that was a little odd. The service was a little spotty, there was only gentleman working that I could see. He was nice enough but barely said anything when he took our order and after when we paid. I also ordered a green tea that was forgotten about, and when I asked about it, he just went to get it without saying anything. However the food was really good and made up for all of the other awkwardness. I had a dosa which I've never tried before, but it was really tasty. Super happy they have so many vegetarian options, so I will for sure be coming back.

I've been meaning to write a review for months.  After having received gift cards for this place over a year ago I'm ashamed I did not try here sooner. It's very small but that's typical of your Philadelphia "gastro pub" feel. Their menu is surprisingly large for such a small place. I had a hard time deciding what I wanted because everything sounded delicious. Our waitress was sweet, engaging and attentive!  I loved to find out their chef makes all of their items from scratch. You can tell it's all extremely fresh. Since going here I have fantasies and dreams about their mac and cheese and dry rub wings. Seriously- such a great place!  The only downside, I don't live closer!

Wonderfully convenient to the Boise metro area (~40 minutes driving on icy roads during peak times from the North End).  My brother-in-law and I went on the Sunday after New Year's for an afternoon of cross-country skiing, and there was ample parking, helpful staff, awesome views and very well-maintained trails.  $21 total for an afternoon pass and rentals.
It was a very family friendly environment and have delicious food. You should go there anytime after Long days at work you're enjoying it already
Movegreen is an amazing company! They provide great service and give back to our community. I definitely recommend using them! Thank you Movegreen!

Parking garage located in the heart of the action. Very close to independence Hall and all of Philadelphia's big tourist attractions.

Garage is clean, secure, well maintained, with abundant spaces. Spaces are not overly tight. 

 Be sure to bring your ticket with you after you park. You will need it to get back into the garage and you will need to pay before exiting. This  is a good security measure, as it keeps the riff raff out of the garage.

Neighborhood is safe, well lit, and well populated. 

Prices are quite reasonable. I parked for many hours for a little over $20 on a Saturday. 24 hours for $24, which is a bargain. by many big city standards.

This is my go to parking garage whenever I go into downtown philadelphia.
FAVORITE RESTAURANT EVER!!! They are so nice and the food is bomb.... don't @ me... orgasmic chicken and  broccoli  yumm yumm YUM!  such a chill vibe in there, go and see for yourself.

I'm not a big beer drinker, but I have to admit the Flaming Stone beer was good.

The BBQ chicken pizza (Germantown purist) was fine - the BBQ sauce was tasty, but I thought the toppings were a little skimpy and the pizza itself was kind of petite.

Nice festive atmosphere, but definitely on the loud side. 

Service was totally fine by national standards, but a bit distant and businesslike by Nashville standards. (I did like that the waiter split the check without my friend and I even having to ask.)

Good people watching in Hillsboro Village if you can get a window seat in the bar area. 

Based on other Yelp reviews, sounds like I'll have to go back at some point and try the bread pudding and maybe the grouper sandwich.

ps - To Boscos management, you might want to fix the handle in the men's room so that the urinal actually flushes. And (lesser importance) maybe think about repainting the scuffed men's room door so that it matches the stylish decor in the rest of your restaurant. Some of that newfangled technology (infrared paper towel dispenser, automatic faucet, etc.) would also be welcome in the restroom.

UPDATE - After a bit of pondering, I've decided to take away a star based on my recollection of 'the fly problem'. Sitting at the front near the bar, I spent a good portion of the meal swatting away bold flies and/or watching them land on nearby diners. Not very appetizing and probably not very sanitary. Hope that Bosco's can get a handle on this problem.

This restaurant is PHENOMENAL!  All homemade meats and pastries- YUM. My daughter couldn't get enough of the breakfast potatoes and the mimosa options were fabulous. I was not hung over but I highly recommend "the cure."

HIGHLY RECOMMEND
Great nail salon. Justin is my go to person. My no-chip manicure and pedicure are always perfect! . My nails always look great.

If you read any of my info, you'll notice i like to toy around in the kichen throwing dough is one of my favorite past times. but when i'm in a pinch and need a quick cheap pizza, papa murphy's runs a close second. My wife and I love the delight Herb Chicken Mediterranean deLITE®...wow! you know, now that i'm thinking about it, this is sometimes even better than the ones i make. the olive oil/garlic base with the feta and sun dried tomatoes with fresh spinach leaves create a crescendo of flavor. i could seriously eat 3 of these pizzas by myself. 

the service is what you would expect from a short order take home pizza place. mostly teenagers, but they have always been quick and nice so no complaints here. 

if you're in the mood for pizza and don't want to make one from scratch (or pay a buttload) check this place out, it is almost the same price as a frozen pie, but significantly better!!!!

I recently bought a Indo-Persian area rug at an auction. It was dirty, dull and it stunk. Gave it for cleaning at this location. The price tag for cleaning was a bit expensive than I thought. I got my rug in a week. Money well spent! Very professional and knows what they do. I don't have a before picture but will post one that I took now.

If you're entertained by gambling as an end in itself - if you enjoy spending an evening actually trying to win some money - Western Village is really one of the best places in Reno.

For example, there's a poker pay table "10/7 Double Bonus Poker." that, if played perfectly, returns 100.7% of your money. Since casinos rarely like to lose money, it's extremely rare to run across. I found it at Western Village, on the 50-play machines. And they weren't even advertising it - they just slipped it in.

Sadly, I guess too many people caught on, and they eventually reduced it to 9/6/5 - which is still an almost 98-percent payback. Good enough that you really don't need to walk in expecting to lose.

Same goes for the tables - you're usually going to find pretty much the least restrictive rules that you can find in a Nevada casino.

This place doesn't have a lot of glitz or glamour, it doesn't have much in the way of comps, but it's a great place to gamble.

I used this place 3 times because I really needed my wheelchair repaired. The first two times he took my payment but took forever to get my wheelchair back.  The third and last time I used him, my wheelchair was too old for repair, so he sold me a used one supposedly in good condition, the footplates were terrible and said he'll order me new ones but he never did, the wheelchair was in terrible condition and it felt like it was going to fall apart as I was using it; and of course he took the payment for the wheelchair and took forever to bring it to me.  Then after two to three weeks of using the wheelchair, it broke and was unusable; I called him 100 times to comes and repair it and he'll say he'll come that afternoon and would never show up, then the next day he would have a poor excuse of his truck not working. He never brought me the footplates and never came back to repair the crappy wheelchair he sold me.  Stay away from this place if you want to avoid frustrations, headaches, and being ripped off.

Possibly the worst post office ever, employees taking breaks while there are hour longs lines and not picking up any phones calls whatsoever. Completely misinformed about a number of things important to their job. Avoid this place at all costs
From the atmosphere, to the service, to the steak it just doesn't get much better than Flemings. It has become our go to choice for special occasions and it has yet to disappoint.
Awesome!!  The staff goes above and beyond!!!  Thank you Nick!!!  The veal parm was delicious, the service impeccable .

Pumpernick's is a solid lunch spot! It always welcomes quite the crowd, so you may have to wait a bit, but the wait is never long. The menu is vast, so there's something for everyone. Their portion sizes are also huge, so you'll never leave hungry. Save room for the pickle bar too - it's the best! The staff is also friendly and the service is fast (but not like you're being pushed out the door). I recommend if you're looking for a casual and consistently satisfying experience!

Renovated nice atmosphere 
Good price point 
Good customer service is timely 
Free KOFFEE refills (that's how every place should be) 
Food portion - American

Our cashier by the name of "Lady Karen" is a real Karen. First impression of her was when she decided to yell at an old man to put his own things on the conveyor belt. This would be no issue had I not seen the other registers loading the items for the other customers. Also, you don't need to yell. After that was done my husband happened to be holding my Costco membership for me as I was digging through my bag for my credit card, she then proceeded to ask him for his membership when I was standing right there. She raised her voice at me and told me that I needed to pay with a card with the same name as my membership. Lady, I know that. Will you wait a moment while I fish my card out? I'm sorry I didn't have it ready. She then proceeded to make me take out more cards to prove it was really me. Then she rolled her eyes while practically throwing the receipt at me, no "thank you have a nice day". Lazy Karen, you are rude. The extra star is for the rest of the employees.

We researched for months to find the right home when moving to Indy from Los Angeles and I am so glad we have found it! The apartments are gorgeous, the management team is the best, the maintenance staff is so friendly and prompt to respond to any issues, and I've met some amazing residents who have become great friends! Our initial plan was to rent for a year and then look for houses to buy but I'm trying to put that off for as long as possible because I absolutely LOVE living here!!

If you are looking for an awesome brunch, you do not have to look any further.  The place is small, but we came here on a weekday so no problems getting in.  I was on vacation in New Orleans, so I had never been there or heard of the place before.  The menu is full of creative dishes, lots of vegetarian for those who need it.  I personally ordered the Migas w/ Chorizo, but it was between that and about five other items on the menu that also sounded amazing!  The Migas with Chorizo was awesome!  What a lucky find!  I personally promise you that you will not be disappointed.  Odds are highly in my favor that I will be correct.

I scheduled a COVID test at 3 pm and had to wait for 1 hour cause there were walk ins ahead of me. Like what? What's the point of scheduling then? And on top of that u have to wait another 40 min for a physician to come talk to me? Like why all they said that I had to wait 1-3 business days for my results like I already know that. What's the point of even making an appointment 3 days in advanced to wait 2 hours cause of walk ins. This is embarrassing

God forbid their vet T.O practice professionalism or compassion Never....ever....ever.....again!!!! I didn't even want to put 1 star but I had to on Yelp to say something!

STAY AWAY!

Excellent food and prices are reasonable.  Very creative tacos. My wife had the Baja fish taco. Got it Mojo style which is more spicy. I had the brisket taco. Pretty good size tacos. You might only need one. Only one concern. The servers all stick their bare hand in the chip bucket. Saw many servers fix their hair, wipe sweat off their head and then put that same hand in the chip bucket. Gross. Just put some tongs in there!!  When you see something like that you wonder what other sanitary issues there might be.

Simply, one of the better choices of restaurants at the Opry Mills Mall.  I would much rather eat here than at the food court or Fridays.  In my opinion, it's a little over priced for tex-mex.  The cheese dip is really good and the tortilla soup was okay.  I believe the tortilla soup was considered a signature dish but I didn't really notice anything  signature about it.  

The atmosphere is a little funky and upbeat.  I can see where this would be a great place to bring the kiddos!
The lunch buffet is intoxicatingly delicious. It raises the bar for Indian food in Nashville.

If I could give 0 stars I would. I used to love this place so much but after coming yesterday and finding a finger nail in my drink I will never return. I felt something in my MOUTH and it was the nail. I spit it out, ran to the bathroom and washed my mouth out. I then put the nail in a paper towel to bring up to the worker and tell them about it ( I made sure to be quiet so no one could hear ) and the worker had major attitude about it. She had fake nails and said she made the drink so she didn't know how that happened. I told her I know it wasn't her nail and I didn't know either. All of a sudden this situation turned around on me as if I would put my own finger nail in my drink just for a refund. Very disappointed in the situation and not once did I receive and apology. I will be telling everyone about my poor experience and to avoid this location

Ok so this is favorite bakery of all time! The only reason why they're not getting five stars is because I can't my donuts anymore!!! Everything here is great, the cookies, pies, cakes and yes the awesome donuts. Due to COVID-19 no donuts...what!?! Can't wait until they're back...

Whatchu know about pierogies?! Every item at Mom-Mom's is like heaven in your mouth. I'm so excited that Philly has a new kid on the block and it's AMAZING. We follow them on facebook to stay updated on their current offerings and location. No more traveling to Port Richmond to get your polish fix, people... Mom Mom's is taking over NoLibs.... GO GET IT.

An OK location to see a concert. Exactly the same as the Knitting Factory was beforehand with a balcony and main floor area. I would much rather see a show at Cargo nearby as that is a way better music venue. That being said it is nice that the Virginia Street Brewhouse attract bands that can't fill up larger spots like the GSR.
