Casino Del Sol is a five star resort. My husband is a member of their Player's Club. You do get some great perks. Every month there is free play, a meal credit, usually free rooms and more. Then there are the invitation only parties. They are nicely done. This night we were celebrating Dia de Las Muertas. There were tequila drinks, champagne, wine, beer and a delicious street taco bar with three kinds of meat, flour tortillas, salsa, chips and guacamole. Free prizes included free play and two beautiful limited edition bottles of Patron. To me every bottle of Patron is a work of art. We didn't win the Patron but Jim scored $100 of free play. Fun evening.

Foie Gras seems to be raw and it is very bitter. Not recommended. Smoked octopus is okay but the scallop is very tough. Caesar salad is okay, not different from anywhere else. Duck leg is okay but the beans in it seems to be from cans.

It's better than 5 guys. And I love 5 guys' burgers. I said it and I'm not ashamed!!!


I went in for the first time today and am hooked. It's a little pricy ($11 for a cheeseburger w bacon and a fountain soda) but it's delicious.  I'll definitely be a repeat customer!

Amazing! I've had King Ribs hundreds of times, but haven't in about 6 months. I ordered a tip dinner w/ mild sauce. The ribs had a great smoky flavor and there was a good balance of crunchy bits, reminiscent of burnt ends, and  fattier pieces. 

On the contrary, the Mac n cheese lacked flavor. It tasted more like boiled noodles.
abura soba - BEST DISH!!!  Flavorful like you wouldn't believe!!  Fantastic service too.

Cool grocery, liquor, souvenir, and surf shop. It's across the street from the Springhill & Residents Inn By Marriott and carries a lot of the thing you'll need and want. I've gone there for drinks, water, and snacks and have gotten great service each and every time.

They have a variety of snacks, food items, and full liquor, not just beer and wine. 

Don't be fooled because at the middle of the store is a full surf simulator that you can either watch or participate in. It's cool seeing people wipe out while I'm picking out some essentials for the beach.

The prices are average so no surprise if a few things are a little more expensive at the beach. Great store to shop at.

I am giving Harrah's 3 1/2 stars but this format doesn't allow for half stars.  The hotel staff were nice and friendly, my room was clean as was the hotel and casino.  Some issues I ran across. The bed was completely broken down on the side were the phone sat creating a huge dip. I rolled over in my sleep and kept rolling into this dip and had to catch myself from falling off the bed.  You have to pay for WI-Fi which is rediculous your a casino.  Being a tall man 6'2" it sucked to have the shower head down at my chest.  This I don't understand at all if one is shorter the water still gets to you. Shower heads need to be about a foot higher. There was black mold in the shower/ceiling in several spots.  The toilet is so close to the toilet paper holder it poked into my legs when I needed to use it.  Lastly I went to make coffee my first morning I lifted the top to pour water in and saw a whitish substance coating the interior of the water reservoir. I thought calcium build up so I washed my hands and ran my finger over this substance.  It wasn't scale or calcium it felt greasy or oily.  I was completely grossed out and didn't use it.  Who knows what some I'll minded individual put in there. See photos of all I've talked about. Oh one final thing, get a room on a high floor if possible the views are spectacular and the street and casino noise are greatly reduced.
This place has a really cool vibe and I really enjoy the open space. The beer is great too! Overall it just has a really cool atmosphere and I will definitely be coming back

I booked an appointment for my parent's dog since they are older and unable to properly wash their dog. The owner texted me because that seems to be the only way she communicates.  She confirmed a 9:00am appointment on a Saturday.  She was two hours late and never reached out either by text or phone call.  My parents reached out to me and I texted the owner who apologized that she was running behind!  She arrived at 11:05am but was not apologetic and just asked for the dog.  She never introduced herself to me or my parents.  She was not wearing a mask and my parents are over the age of 65.  They had their masks on but were uncomfortable that she did not.  She also said she only accepts cash or check which I had left my credit card for my parents to pay her. This information should have been explained when I made the appointment. I feel she is very unprofessional. In 2020 not to accept credit cards with all that is going on and not wear a mask!  She also still charged us $80 even though she was late and we were new customers.  We will never use her again.

The food was good but $30 per adult and  $20 for kids was a bit much. I'm glad we came to try it but after 2 adults and a kid with drinks the $100+ tab at the end made me feel like it's not worth it. You can go somewhere else and spend that kind of money and feel like it was better spent. Definitely did not eat $100 worth of food. The staff was super friendly though and the service was great.

We usually love this place. Sunday night, not so much. Not many people in to eat but plenty of staff. 
Several things on the menu were either not available or the wait person came much later to tell me they ran out of something. They put Italian dressing on my husband's salad along with a side of Ranch (which is what he asked for.) My daughter's order was wrong so they comp'd us on that. The food was not as good as we are used to. Keep trying guys, we'll see you in a few months.

We hoped to find someone with a Saturday happy hour starting around 3:30 or 4.  Amazingly enough, Bar Ly has a Saturday happy hour from 3:30 to 6:30.  So that was good.  Unfortunately, the cocktails were mostly, or entirely, pre-made, so, while the intriguing-sounding Luscious Lychee Martini can't be blamed on Bar Ly directly --  they are guilty of serving it.  "Worse than drain-cleaner," my wife said after tasting the one I had ordered.  Don't know how she knows, but I suspect she is right.  I couldn't drink even half of it, and felt nauseated for another hour after.  I had tried a glass of Riesling before that, but it was sour-tasting.  Meanwhile, a woman down the bar a few places couldn't put three words together without an S- or an F-curse, which got old fast.  There are loads of TVs around, but as luck would have it, the one in front of us was showing skinny bizarros weighing in for kick-boxing bouts or something.  Three strikes, we were out of there.  The second star above is added because at least Bar Ly is trying with those happy hour times.

Tried this place three times in last three years. Food is just awful. I am pretty easy to please when it comes to restaurants but they are consistently bad. Service is slow. Food is bland. Move on for other Mexican options.

Another great place for coffee, beneigts, baked goods, and breakfast. We had lattes & beneigts for a snack early afternoon. There's also a garden seating area. I want to come back to try one of their egg dishes.
Delicious, Good prices, & light on the tummy! I had their one non-vegetarian meal item of the day, and it was incredible!

I love Juju. Every time is wonderful. Really good hair stylists, and the vibe is genuine fun!  
I have allergies problems with any product with too much of artificial fragrances, Juju has the best products, organics and with natural fragrance.  My hair looks wonderful!

So its nice and all but seems kind of outdated still? This maybe done on  purpose but I dont get the elegance I expect from a place of this nature. The bar was wicked , service was awesome real quick. The rooms seemed crammed though. The tv was tiny and the honeyroom suites meh..I have definetly seen better. For the dollars its not worth but because Im from Edmonton I though I would stay at one of our historiacal buildings. Be wary of parking too it costed me $55 for the night.

This food was absolutely amazing! I can't wait to go back!! There was not one dish that I didn't thoroughly enjoy. My hubby and I had the Indiana Field Greens salad, the lobster special, and the shrimp & grits. We topped it off with the parfait and hoecakes for dessert...scrumptious!!!

Best sushi we've had in Philly, and we go out for sushi a good deal.  Umai Umai is small, and a reservation is needed for a weekend night even just for two, but the atmosphere is warm and inviting and intimate.  Great place for a first date, I'd think.  Prices are about the same as other good sushi restaurants, but the presentation and combination rolls out perform other restaurants.  Waitstaff were very accommodating and rearranged seating to give us a nicer spot.  Outdoor seating when weather is warm.  Not a very convenient location but worth the shlep.

Babysitting the grandkids and all they wanted for lunch was Cane's chicken! This restaurant is a step above most fast food restaurants. The chicken tenders are plump and juicy, made with white meat. Most meals are served with French fries and Texas toast and a delicious dipping sauce which my grandson dipped everything in including the toast! I love their iced tea-offered in sweet and unsweetened. I like this restaurant better than their competitors and they've been consistently good on every visit.

So absolutely yummy! I'm drooling just thinking of the ricotta and honey.

Only negative was the bathrooms were atrocious. However the food was so good, I'll still give 5 stars.

The menu is pretty standard. That said, the food was always so satisfying and reliable that I always kept coming back for more. My healthy comfort food, if you will. The service was always a nice added bonus. My only regret is not letting myself try everything on the menu despite my number of visits here. I miss having you around the corner.
Over price ! They charge you for Trial  pair of contacts lens ! Over charge on the exam also !!!!

The Philly steak here is definitely a Philly steak, and not bad at all, but if you're looking for Gino's or Pat's you may be disappointed. It's not quite up to the standard of the best Philly steaks in the area either. But again, it's pretty good. The roll is very nice, there's a decent amount of meat, and you get your choice of the usual toppings, although the toppings aren't quite up to what I'm used to at other places that offer Philly steak sandwiches. On top of that, the service is very good, friendly enough and I didn't have to wait very long, even at lunch time. The parking is a little scarce, but there is a parking lot in the back, if you can find it. To review, not great, but pretty good.

The food is good but it comes at a cost. Their food has so much sodium it's insane. After I saw the sodium content of their foods from their website I am def not going back. The average meal has at least 2500mg of sodium. Your arteries won't thank you down the road. This place is def not for the health freaks.

Not a friendly staff. You have to ask for your receipt if you want it or they will never give it to you. When you do ask for it, they get frustrated with you. I like Starbucks but I have to avoid this one if I can.

I actually go to this place because there is a pretty decent mini Subway Restaurant inside.  The staff at the Subway is always friendly and quick about getting your order out.  The only draw back is the fact that it is inside the gas station and you pay for your order at the gas station counter.  The cashiers for the gas station are not as friendly.  Also, I wish that the drink station for the Subway fountain drinks was separate from the gas station drink and coffee.  This area tends to get a little messy with people spilling coffee and sugar.  

All in all, if you happen to be on that western most end of Cypress street and you want a quick, healthy, affordable meal that will allow you to get in and out without a hassle or long lines, this is it.  No frills.

I stopped by the other day (I was in the area), and will definitely have to come back! It is absolutely the best pho in town. It is fresh, and the flavors are far more complex and interesting than the pho at other places I've tried. Oh! The spring rolls were also fantastic! The atmosphere is welcoming, and the staff is phenomenally attentive and friendly. Even though this place is extremely far from me, I will have to return soon.
Lived coming here on Sundays and decided to stop by on my way back from Lambertville!  Fun atmosphere!

Like the new menu. Miss the Cromwell burger. The Southwest chopped salad is delicious. I have not ventures to the Mexican food side of the menu lately. I did have the Patty Melt and Turkey Reuben and both were very good.

I am not completely and totally sold on this place yet. I went in and told the place I'd like a pedi and nail fill and they did quickly seat me. They didn't ask which pedicure I wanted, so they did their own thing, which was actually fine but had I wanted something different and was preoccupied or something, (sometimes I'm making appointments on my phone as I get my toes done), I would've been upset. They did a good job with them, but my right big toenail broke in 3 days, and that was with gel polish on. So, I was a little upset about that. 
Then, moving onto the nails. They could tell I was wearing pink & white so they had the products used for that, but didn't ask me what shade of pink I wanted, didn't ask me if I wanted my nails cut down, and they shaped them how they wanted them. I had to speak up and tell them to cut them down and shape them the way I wanted and he didn't seem too excited about a customer telling him what they wanted. :-/ the guy was gentle, and did a good job which is always good in my book. I am going back and I will do another update when I do.

 Update:: I went back today (previous review was from Oct 2021). The owner (I guess he's the owner since he does all the calls), was super friendly and in a great mood. I walked in and told him I wanted a pedi and my pink and white nails to be switched to gel polish. He didn't have any problems with it at all. So, I had my pedi done and the girl who did them was very quiet and didn't speak a word...that's fine. I don't mind a quiet person because I'm one who actually doesn't talk much (believe it!) she did good but I assume I either didn't have any ingrown nails or she didn't dig them out - one or the other..:but she was gentle and it was putting me to sleep lol. 

Onto the nails. The girl was ok...not the best but also not the worst.  She did good about not hurting me, she asked me if I wanted square nails and I said yes but they're square rounded. I don't like that. She tried to haggle me into getting dip power, and I don't like dip powder and at first she wasn't taking no for an answer, but she might've picked up on my annoyance and stopped. She didn't say much after that. I love the color, and I love gel polish and I think that's where I'm going to stop from how on. The other stuff isn't for me. 

All in all, I will stick at 3 stars.

A quaint/adorable/awesome French restaurant where prices are fair and the food is fantastic. The mussels are a must-have. Everyone raves about the crepes, and the dinner specials are usually fantastic. 

I've never been here without having to wait at least a little while, but you get in pretty quickly, and can have a reasonably-priced drink at the bar.

Got into New Orleans this evening. We read so many reviews on places and decided to eat at Gumbo Shop. Line was super long, so we walked down the street to this place. They told us to seat ourselves and the waitress came by about ten minutes later and took our drink order and food order. She came back quite a bit later to drop off our drinks and reeked of weed. Apologized that she had "gotten busy" and that's why we hadn't gotten our drinks. Then, she brought out our three dishes at separate times. I got the Cajun Combination. Gumbo was suppppper bland. Jambalaya was dry dry dry dry, especially the chicken. I had to use the "Louisiana Hot Sauce" on the table to make it less rubbery. The crawfish pie was very good and redeemed any hope I had on eating a decent meal that night. We asked if the order could be split and the waitress kind of snapped back that they couldn't. We told her it was COMPLETELY fine and handed her a credit card. She came back with the menu, stuck it in my face, and pointed at the part where it said as of January they couldn't split tickets. Couldn't wait to leave that place. Food was crap and service was crap. Heed my warning! I don't reviews often, especially negative ones. Rough start to our trip!

The menu has expanded quite a bit since they opened.  Burritos, chimichanga, flautas, and tortas.  

Great guacamole and some of my favorite queso.  Try a taco special or something different.

Bought GE fridge kept breaking down.  Asked for full refund.  Flatly refused.  Kept explaining why you can't return refrigerators when you can return everything else including cars.  Slipped in fine print that held us to that we never signed. Haughty and condescending.  Seemed to delight in the fact we were unaware of fine print.  Offered no solution.  This is place is terrible place never go here.

We just had a somewhat disappointing meal. Our server, Jennifer, was great. We were really excited for the Eggs Benedict but the eggs were hard. They had clearly been sitting out for a while. The onion rings were cold, too, but they replaced them. We go to Galatoire's six or seven times a year and feel like they recognize us. It did not feel like that today...a disappointment for our Fathers Day meal.
On a quick overnight stop this near the hotel.  Great food, good prices with big servings.  Definitely a do over.  The pizza is great, just really not big enough to share.

Great Thai food! The mixed appetizer was wonderful (with a couple substitutions). It says for two but can easily feed three/four. The curries and noodles were great. Without changing the spiciness level, the food came out with perfect heat. Service is a bit slow but worth the wait. Also, call ahead if you think it will be busy to make a reservation.

Dined here earlier this year. The breakfast was good and our server Richard was excellent. Everything was going fine UNTIL Dominique or Monique (or whatever her name was) stepped in with her poor and envious attitude. Her service was lackluster and to top it off when we checked our bill after we left we noticed this B not only charged us for the meal but also doubled almost the entire meal charge by adding up the other receipt with a room charge when we weren't even staying there! We're sorry that you have no desire or interest in your job, but that was your life decision and you don't have to have a poor attitude towards paying customers who clearly are more educated than you and aren't stupid enough to fall for that. We even called the restaurant to have the charges removed and the person who picked up the phone said the manager wasn't there but that they would call back. NO ONE ever called back SO clearly even management is a bust here. Come pull these kinds of stunts at an LA restaurant and you will be fired instantaneously. Called the bank and had the extra charges removed.  We will never come back to this place. EVER. 

As Natalie mentioned below, SOME of the staff here are crooks who add on an extra charge to your bill to tip themselves 50% or more. I have no reason to make this up. Clearly this is a common practice at this place. Don't eat here unless you want to be served with attitude and a bill that's been up-charged. Sickening behavior by a poorly trained staff.

I don't know how this place has such rave reviews: Hostel is in a sketchy neighborhood. To pay off your room you have to use cash unless your balance is more than $80. Bathrooms are coed and the staff is rude. If you are allergic to cats, there is a cat named Taj who lives in the hostel. The beds are uncomfortable as well as the blankets, and the whole place is hot as there is no air conditioning, even in November when we stayed. If you want to store bags the only option is to leave them in the living area unattended. There is a lot of noise at all hours of the night and day, the walls are paper thin, and the doors have a tendency to slam. There were holes in our room's floor that led to the ground outside. I was afraid it was going to go out from under me as it was patched up in a quick manner and not very stable. We clocked in an hour and a half after the check in time and the guy showing us our room casually said "Oh, I hope they cleaned it". There is so much more wrong with this place than right, the only redeeming thing is the courtyard is kind of cool. DO NOT STAY HERE, and don't say I didn't warn you.

Our (adult) kids treated us to dinner here before their concert at the Bowl, so we were seated at 5:30. We had the fried cauliflower,(cauliflower, how could that be any good? OMG!) I was able to consume nearly the entire plate while the others were fighting over calamari in black ink, (which I named "Squink"); a very nice arugula and sliced artichoke heart salad, and a delicate meatball dish. Then the pizzas; my daughter and I consider ourselves experts on this, both adept at making them from scratch, often, so this was a test. We agreed: excellent. The right sauce, correct amount, balanced amount of interesting ingredients, excellent crust with a good yeasty bubble to it. Fine service by a pleasant waitstaff. The lost 5th Star? My only real complaint was the sound level: by 6:30 room levels had elevated, we were shouting at each other, and we had the added treat of listening to an older actor at the next table read the ENTIRE menu to his date.

We can't get enough of this place.  Love the Zaatar pita, falafel, chicken shawarma, baba ghannuj, hummus.  The Syrian fries are also amazing, but don't get them as takeout.  Most of the time we order different entrees so we can share and enjoy all the flavors!
Who hurt these baristas? What's with the miserable attitude? Is someone holding a gun to their head and forcing them to work there? Hey sour ass baristas, blink twice if you need help

I was in the Clearwater area and was craving for something sweet. Mint Fox was just a few minutes away so I decided to give it a try. The man working was very nice! When you walk into the store, you instantly get hit with that delicious scent of cookies!!! 

I ordered a cookies n cream with vanilla sprinkles. Super good and really hit the spot! My friend got a sundae and she said it was also really good. I couldn't resist so I bought a chocolate chip cookie to go and I'm so glad I did. The cookie's texture was chewy but also a little crispy. I would definitely return to Mint Fox if I ever visited Clearwater again!

I live in NY and recently "lost" my brother-in-law who lived in Florida. I called Hayes Florist to order an arrangement for his birthday to be sent to the cemetery where he was interred . Amanda was very understanding, compassionate and helpful . My family was as satisfied with the arrangement as I was with the service! 
( The Family Service Counselor at Memorial Park Cemetery sent me a picture ). We will definitely us this florist again! Thank you Amanda !

Love love love Euphoria! I had my hair cut last night for the first time at Euphoria and I love it. The salon is in an older, cute, charming house. Very intimate, charming and fun atmosphere. Linda is a great stylist, with an obvious passion for hair. I highly recommend her! I have already scheduled my next appointment. You better get on her schedule soon because she books up fast!

I was reviewed here by a friend and have never looked back. The entire staff is amazing, no matter who is sitting at the desk when I come in there's friendly conversation. The services are always top-notch, the conversation during the services is great, and I'm always happy with the outcome. They work really hard to make their customers happy and I would recommend them to anyone looking for a new salon.

My usual services are eyebrows and bikini+ waxing. The one time I got a blowout I was very happy with that outcome as well.

Does anybody know why they close? The food was always on point. 
It really sucks specially when the food is good!

The scenes from Top Chef kept teasing me; I swear it.

As of last month (12/15), one must start using bus line 12 to continue to Uptown area. The line stops in the Garden across the street from  the upscale Fresh Market. 

$1.25 for one ride, or $3/all day pass, $9/3 day pass.

These cars were built in 1923-24. To show off how impressive the quality of the mahogany and brass are: front riding seats alter via a slide along a track to become backs, depending upon whether one wants to sit facing one another. Coolest feature...amazing ingenuity, even back then!

Very convenient, romantic riding in the Big Easy. Passes through the Arts/Warehouse, Lee Circle, and Garden District. 

I loved it. Can get to Cochon and Peche this way... as well as to the Audobon Zoo, etc. 

We even walked to Rouse's from the Julia stop on this line! Had to get our King cake on.

PS Don't forget the Esplanade line along the river to get one to Frenchmen! We took a cab, though. too tired!
One of my favorite neighborhood eateries :) Consistently great service and food . There is also great live music .

I visit Anthony's for lunch at least once a week and I'm never disappointed! Tons of vegan/vegetarian options but they also have meat for the non-compassionate eater ;) I love their daily specials and how fresh all their veggies are. If you like healthy, tasty food then Anthony's Dandelion Deli is a great place to eat.
My favorite place to go for pho. Amazing food, affordable prices and good atmosphere. I'll keep going back for pho!

Some of the worst customer service and human interaction I've ever seen. So Sad. At Philadelphia International Airport, 90% of the restaurants and coffee shops remain closed. One of the few places open was La Colombe Coffee. Naturally there was a line. I stood in line for 30-40 min for a coffee and people were very nice and well behaved. As I approached the front of the line the 2 employees spent plenty of time talking to each other about personal, non-work related stories, but the moment the lady in front of my asked a question about the coffee or the food items available the guy says "Jesus Christ, is the time for questions? No it's not..." then he trails off while complaining about his CUSTOMERS!! Who just had reasonable questions since they didn't have all the items listed on the menu! 

Can you guys get rid of these workers and hire some people Who actually value having a Job? People who take pride in what they are doing - whether that means managing or making coffee? 

This is the worst place I've ever seen. 3 Thumbs down. Don't waste your money here.
The store staff was arrogant, rude and insulting.  I was badgered and cut my shopping experience short.  Might have just been my individual treatment.  However, I did like the specialized inventory.
Awesome sand which! Perfectly executed, cheese meat and their special olive dressing is amazing!

If you're going to have a dress code. Management should be smart enough to put what the dress code on a sign outside. This is a bar and grill. But tank tops are not allowed. I was told that wife beaters were not allowed. I was wearing a grey tank top. It's professional enough for our company. Not for a bar I guess. Said they would still serve me this time but new owner and I should know the rules for later. When the sweet tea was brought to me. It tasted bad. My buddy who regulars this place agreed and said the tea tasted bad. At that point I left him there and went and ate at The Angry Pepper. I guess they don't have problems with company tank tops there. Can't tell you how the food is now or ever. Hope your experience is better than mine. 3 people in the whole place during lunch rush time. Maybe you should relax a little bit about tank tops. My clothes were not dirty ripped or torn.

Dropped off bike on a Thursday, was told to pick it up the next day but I couldn't so I told them I'd pick it up Saturday. Went there but it wasn't done, was told to come back in an hour. Don't have time to wait so I went back Monday, shop not open due to rain. Staff seemed uninterested in service. Went back at 4 on Tuesday , was still not done and I told them I would take it home. They offered to do it then but I declined. They had plenty of time to get it done or contact me and give me a day it would be done. In my opinion that is not how you do business. That also told me good luck finding another shop to do the work. You had your chance. Not going back. They lost my business.
Add on: see owner's response. Will give them another try as he admits that this could have been handled better and he is not making excuses. I appreciate that, he also reached out to me personally. To continue.
Good food at a cool little hole in the wall market, they also sell hookahs and maybe allow you to hookah there? Anyway the food was quite fresh and good and a great price.

Lets just say that I received the best massage by Kristen that I ever had by far. I never had a Thai massage, despite my wife raving how great they are. I finally listened to my wife and saw Kristen and then went and thanked my wife for pushing to get one. Her professionalism and knowledge were unbelievable. I never felt so relaxed and at peace during a message before. I am always so tense from how deep people go. But not her, she really listened to what I told her in the beginning of the session and knew just how hard to go. I am not an expert on messages but sure had enough of ones to know she is the real deal. I will not look for any one else any more. I will be a regular client for sure. Oh and by the way, now a few days later I still feel amazing. Thanks Kristen for awesome message you gave. I will tell all my friends about your Transformational Movement.

Went to try this place over lunch, as I've heard very good reviews of it. Our waitress was very nice, and when we placed our orders, they come with soup/salad, and bun/roll. We ordered the vegetarian dishes, and our waitress advised us that the soup had chicken broth in it. I was very happy to be informed of that, and I made sure she got a good tip for being observant and considerate. The MerLion Noodle had the best noodles I've ever had, thin and just crispy enough. The Mussaman Curry was so sweet and delicious, with perfect cuts of potatoes and tofu. This place has taken the spot for my favorite Thai restaurant.
It's a little more expensive than most places but worth it. My acrylics have stayed on for over a month which is unheard of! No breaking, no lifting, no chipping- just perfect nails for a month!

Have yet to try the burger here...supposed to be good.

I have never had good service from the bartenders.   Never.  Actually on one stop in, I waited about 10 minutes with no acknowledgement,  and left.

I've never seen a huge crowd here, likely coming on off nights.  

I'll give the burger a shot, but am don't have great expectations.

Nice building,  hip decor, well meaning staff. Slow service,  lousy cocktails,  but you can get healthy food and fresh squeezed juices... eventually. .. if the things on the menu are still actually on offer because as the water told us "Well, It's kind of a new place, we've only been open two years, so we're still trying to see what works, so some of the stuff on the menu wasn't selling, so we don't have it anymore."  A statement to inspire confidence. 

After my friend  bit into what was either an olive pit or an olive pit sized rock in her turkey wrap our party of four was over it. 
If you have a lot of time to kill, are not particularly hungry or thirsty and are looking for healthier options that may or may not be available,  then this could be your place.

Wow.  Absolutely RUDE "customer service". Little brunette employee insanely awful... Scowling face and ugly attitude.  
Don't go on the front door as you have to sign in at the back door... yet no sign to tell you that so you get berated for coming in as a normal person would.
Tasty steak sandwich. Not really a ton of meat but okay. Fries were okay also. Not too sure what all the fuss is about to be honest.  But it was good for a quick lunch

Been here twice and the first time, I had a regular milk tea with boba. I liked that it wasn't sweet but the boba tasted kinda watered down. This time, I got the matcha milk tea and it's pretty good! It's a cute little cafe with some bench seating. And I'm pretty sure they are the same as the one in the mall and the midtown location. Great service, clean, and hey have WiFi too, if you're looking for a place to study and enjoy some milk tea.

We love Saffron! We recently did curbside pickup, and they were so accommodating. The gentleman who brought out our food was wearing a mask and very polite. I'm glad they are offering this service during covid as I was craving some Indian food!!

The beef samosas with cilantro sauce are my favorite. My husband always gets the Lamb Vindaloo extra spicy whereas I toned down the spice for my Chicken Tikka Masala.

My son and I, from The Bay Area, had breakfast that morning in Reno at a popular cafe which was highly rated in Yelp. We met a couple  there (locals) and asked them for a dinner recommendation. They immediately highly recommended the "Rattlesnake" Club.  We were not disappointed.  We were warmly greeted by Chanel (5th child in her family)  and we selected outdoor seating. The food was fabulous (chicken pasta dish, and the Rib Eye), and our server Sierra made us feel like royalty!  Upon departure we were in our car and Sierra came running out to us (sprinting) just in time to return my sons cell phone that he had left behind!!  Food & Service, Awesome!!!  Thank you Chanel and Sierra!

I'm giving  the corner bakery three stars because the food does taste good. I've been going there for a long time and most of the time I order the chop salad the larger one in fact. The last few times that I went there I bought the larger salad as always but the bowl was only half filled or should I say half empty. I spoke to the manager I was told that everything is methodically measured per corporate guidelines and that's that. Meanwhile before I ordered there's a sample of the bowls where you place your order a large and a small empty bowl at the top of inside of the bowl there is a blue line. Who knew that this blue line was just a decoration and certainly not a measurement as it appears. Again I had always gotten the full ball and always been happy with it but for $10 I expect more than a half a bowl. I'm a full grown man I weigh over 200 pounds and this delicate salad just doesn't cut the mustard. Again the food definitely tastes good and maybe it's just the salads that are a problem. The people that I went with had sandwiches and they were very happy with them they looked good I'm sure they tasted good this review is about portion I feel that if you're going to spend $10 you should get $10 worth of food and again I'm one of those people that orders the same thing all the time and I had an expectation of a full Bowl and was extremely disappointed. When I wrote t
corporate they were nice enough to send me back a letter with a $10 coupon and told me that they planned on speaking with this particular restaurant the one in Bala Cynwyd and I was happy about that until I called tonight to find out about volume and again everyone there has been nice I spoke with a young man who apparently was the manager this time when I was in the shop last time it was a woman but he told me the same thing that again it's all measured so if you're going to go there I think you can expect good tasting food just don't order the salad it ain't worth $10.

Gentleman Jack's Barber Lounge is a great place to get to take a break and get your hair cut. Joaquin has been cutting my hair and my dad's for some time. He always takes his time, does it right the first time, and goes out of his way to provide quality service. 

The interior is masculine and well done. I highly recommend!

Delicious, hearty vegetarian food that doesn't lack on flavor!

Full disclaimer: eating an entirely vegetarian meal (as a meat eater) is entirely fine by me. That said, my very much meat eating boyfriend is enamored with this place! We tried it out last week and then came back again yesterday! So far we had the Philly steak (twice - the best item in my opinion), the ziggy burger (delicious smoky flavor) and the curry tofu wrap (maybe a little mushy as far as texture but super tasty!). 

Seeing other people's pics of the burger and sandwiches, I was a little hesitant. I thought the bun looked hard and too bready. I was wrong! There is enough sauce on the sandwich and just general delicious juiciness that I didn't expect from a veggie burger that the bread is perfect to stand up to all of it. Definitely our new go-to spot! 

One note though, I would never pay $4 for a whipped banana. I often freeze bananas and blend them at home. It's a delicious treat (tastes like ice cream!) but that price is obscene. Buy a 19 cent banana from trader joes and do it yourself!

Really like this place. It has brisket and does it well, somewhat of a rarity in Nashville. Very tender and a nice char on the outside. Pork has good flavor. Portions are more than enough. They have a rotating list of grits available, and they're rock solid. You won't see the featured grits on the online menu, so if that interests you, wait to order until you're there. It doesn't take long anyway. Sweet heat sauce is very good. Staff is always nice and they're never too busy.

As far as Nashville's taste buds go, some of the food can be a little 'spicy,' but if you have a normal sense of what is spicy and what isn't, it's totally fine.

Hope they stick around.

The wait time was awful!  We were told the wait was 25-30 mins but it ended up being double that.. it was extremely loud inside. we had to have the waitress repeat herself because we couldn't hear her. She started by telling us all the things they were out of including staples for a brunch spot  like tomato, turkey sausage and peanut butter. Food was good but nothing special. We won't be back and wouldn't recommend it.

This place is pretty cool. It has everything you may want in a bar. It has great drinks. Highly recommended their Mezcal cocktails. Food was pretty good and quick service. Atmosphere was dimly lit and a very good vibe. Music wasn't loud which was good. Come here and check it out!

This is located on the pier I wanna say. They have a spacious inside seating with live music and a huge bar or they have a nice more quiet area where you can sit outdoors. Since the weather was nice and not humid or hot we sat outside. Very cool. They also have a separate bar outside so we ordered some Margaritas. The MOD(manager on duty) was named Kevin and he came over and made sure we were comfortable. That was nice, the girl bartenders were nice as well. Noticed they have a lot of regular customers here, that's a good thing. So we ordered come fresh grouper nuggets(when in FL you must order grouper) they are meaty and fresh. SOOOO good they can literally be a meal with a side of fries and salad and hubby ordered a seafood chowder that was sooo good he also took one to go. For our entrees I ordered the blackened grouper sandwich. I didn't care much for the bread but the grouper was good and so were the fries. Hubby ordered the special which was a filet mignon with shrimp and a reduced balsamic sauce. This was delicious!!! The steak was cooked perfectly. We got a Key Lime Pie slice to go and this was a perfect ending to our perfect beginning. Overall we were happy to stop by here and support the locals. Definitely will be returning.

Love the atmosphere, the food was good.  The tortilla chips lack in flavor, as does the salsa, as does the guacamole.  So, EH.

Lindsay, our server, was SUPER NICE!  2 moms & 2 kids went to Sesame Place all day (directly next door), and this was a very wonderful ending to our day.  She took care of us, made suggestions on food, kindly tolerated our indecisive kids tastes, she MADE this visit!!  Can't say enough about her!!!  5 stars PLUS!

Management, on the other hand is AWFUL.  I left my C/C on the booth, in error of course, and called a few minutes later to ask.  Got the run around, got a call back, they had it & will keep it ; I could not come back that night for it!??  I went back the next day & the new manager KYLE had tossed it!!!???  Who does that??  Nobody does that!!!  I live over a half hour away, came all the way back & brought my family...  I even went in that evening to give them more business... had sat down... then had nothing to pay with.  I was livid.  You think the manager on duty (not KYLE this time), to keep the business, would have comp'ed at least MY meal (since my retired mom - who I was with - was going to have to pay for the table of 4, now!!). I finally just asked the manager to comp my meal, but then he was so weird about it.  So forget it... I just left (though my kids had eaten all the free chips & salsa on the table; I tipped the server!).  I was told to write down my name & address & "maybe" something will be sent to me in the mail for a free meal.  Haven't gotten anything a month later.

So basically, management SUCKS.  Awful.  NO TABLESIDE manner.  I will not be returning.  The food was good, but I don't support good food & awful management.  If the food was GREAT, then maybe.  My business will go elsewhere.

This place was top notch. Pulled right in & they went to work! They didn't pressure me or make me feel bad for not purchase any extras. Great protocol for COVID with contactless payment options and everything was very streamlined. I sat in my car the whole time and it only total about 20 minutes. It's awesome to actually watch the work being done to your car opposed to leaving it in the hands a mechanic & picking it up later. I'm impressed and will be back. 

(Also my car is a little bit interesting... the hood is ratchet strapped shut. I was impressed because The manager even went under the hood and re strapped it, then allowed me to check it and make sure it was solid. )

I haven't had any of their food, but the bar scene is fun and hopping.  I'm only giving it three stars because I went with a group of friends, but it was so loud in there that you could only talk to the person right next to you.  I know it depends on the mood you're in and all, but I didn't pick the place.  Our waitress was one of our sorority sisters, which made it fun, and it's the first restaurant I've been to where there was a line of the men's restroom and not the women's.

Wonderfully nice people, however my experience with this business was not very pleasant.  

I dropped off a few suits mid July to get altered - and was greeted by a very pleasant woman who took my measurements and a few notes on how I typically wear my suits.  I was told it would take about 3 weeks before I would be able to pick up the suits.

Fast forward a few weeks and I picked up my suits (without trying them on - big mistake on my part) on the date that was originally promised.  I took them to a business trip two days after picking them up, and that's when I first noticed that the alterations were not done very well.  Specifically one arm was longer than the other, one of the jackets was taken in more than the others, and the hem on the pants was not completed.  Luckily I brought one of my other suits with me so I was able to wear that for my trip, but had I not brought that I would've been in a tough spot. 

I brought the suits back shortly after returning - and the staff immediately apologized for the errors and promised to make it right.  I understand mistakes happen, and having paid for the alterations prior to trying on the work I agreed to have them make the necessary changes.  Again, the people here are extremely nice - however as you'll read momentarily this is where the customer service takes a turn for the worst.  At the time of dropping off the suits (for a second time), I was given another 3 week turnaround.  

On the day that my suits were supposed to be ready, I received a call saying that it will be a few more days - which was completely fine as I was more concerned about the quality of work vs. a quick turnaround time.  I proceeded to come back two weeks after (now 17 days after they said it would be done) and the suits were still not ready.  The staff asked that I return the next day as she had to make a few more changes.  I then dropped in the next morning and much to my dismay - I was told they were still not ready - and I noticed that the staff was working on a completely different garment.  Given the fact that the shop had my clothing for roughly 9~ weeks at this point i would've expected for the staff to have prioritize my order to make it right.  

Finally that afternoon I received a call that my suits were ready to go.. I can't stress this enough, the staff is very kind and I really really wanted them to be my go to alteration shop - however with this sort of service, I will not be returning and will not recommend this place to my family or friends.

Sup Everybody..,Soooo Yeah...Today's Experience at macaroni grill was...Meh! First we waited 15 mins to be seated when there was 3 tables open and no one else was waiting ok no biggie it happens..we get seated our waitress comes takes our drink order brings us bread so far all good right..she comes backs to takes our order all good once again everything is good....THEN....15 mins past..all we get is our refills..then our waitress comes back and asked me what I ordered? ...she said I just wanted to make sure..so I said Chicken paramsan..so at this point am think A she forgot what I ordered B she didn't take down my order considering she took my order first..what ever I let that go as well it happens they were busy..now 25 mins have gone no food yet...the table behind us party of 6 got sat after us a good 10 mins after us..got their food before us..now am starting to get irritated not cool..so a good 35-40 mins later we get our food and it's luke warm..at this point am done I don't even want to eat nor did my niece and sister in law..I took a few bites and I was done same with my niece and sister in law..now we are home and having Actual dinner...That's all folks

It was great till my favorite waxer left. She was tge best!

But during our last appointment both my daughter and I spent hours with tweezers to fix all the hair they missed. I also got burned twice!  When my pass expires I am not sure I will go back. Very expensive for me anyway!

Update: they just called me to try to make it right which I think is very good customer service. Will give them another try and let you know!

This is really close to work so I always use this location. It's a small post office and it can get pretty busy sometimes but the line moves fairly quickly everytime I go. Most of the workers are non expressive so they come off as rude or mean. But they do the job quickly and if you crack a joke or make an effort to converse with them they'll joke back. Customer service jobs sucks so I totally understand the difficulty of keeping a happy face on all day. As long as they aren't obviously rude to you and they get the job done as quickly as possible, give them a break, it's not their job to smile at you or ask about your day. And if you don't have your shit together before you get to the window that's on you, you don't go to the BMV without all your documents and expect them to complete forms for you. Policies sometimes get in the way of practical work so if they say they aren't allowed to stamp "Do Not Bend" (or provide some other service they've done in the past) get over it and move on. You writing it by hand isn't going to kill you.

So disappointed this morning. I planned a fantastic 40th birthday weekend for my husband and it was supposed to end with Sunday brunch at Trenasse for 25 friends traveling from around the world. Except it didn't. When I made my reservation with you weeks ago, you failed to actually complete the process, and then tried to say it was may fault. Major fail. Major disappointment. News Flash. I had my stuff together, you did not. You had 25 people looking forward to what we heard was supposed to be a fabulous meal. Except we didn't. You can rest assured we won't be trying to come back.
Amazing good and friendly staff! I definitely don't recommend missing out on this spot. The boiling spice is by far the best !

AWESOME atmosphere, GREAT food.. Service EHH. Tryst is probably one of the best places on Beach Drive, the outdoor seating, good food and fun, cool atmosphere def draw a crowd. So i'm not sure why their servers can't get it together. On more than one occasion i've been charged twice or charged the wrong total (always more than what I actually spent). I will only use cash at this place from now on. The outside bar seems to always be very slow service. I don't get it :( 

Their business is obviously not hurting, so maybe they just don't care?

Amazing food. I saw a few previous reviews say the price was high but I don't think they understand how the restaurant industry works.

The chips were fresh.
The guacamole was made fresh.

If you want cheap food then it's going to come from a bag. 

You get what you pay for and this is 100% worth every penny.


The tacos were also on point, the tortillas were so soft and light and fluffy and the other ingredients were just as amazing.

The different salsas that came with the ships were all delicious and flavorful.

The tables are well spaced out so it doesn't feel crowded.

Everything about this restaurant is a win. Would visit more often if it were closer to where I live.

Once again you get what you pay for and I feel like I got an amazing meal for the right price. Come and get some amazing food.

Came for girls night and had a fabulous hibiscus martini, guac and chips ( bacon guac was delish!) and the Besa shrimp. My friend ordered ceviche and that was great too. Very attentive waiter too! I'll definitely be back!!

Whoa, tried Detroit style tonight. It's like a pizza but with a cake-like thickness and consistency and this lovely chewy, crunchy cheese coating. We love the new covered tent seating with the string lights, live music and socially distant tables with cute checkered cloths. I'd keep it like this forever!!!

Portions very small, I split a Pear and Bleu cheese salad. Very small for 8.95 we added a chic breast to it for $4.00.  I had a Corned Beef sandwich. It was served on a toasted hoagie roll with not even 4 slices of corned beef on it. It was good and tasty but very small. 9.25. A bud light 4.25. 
Food good
Price to high for portion size.
Great place, tons of fun, our instructor Chris , our instructor was awesome.  Best part is byob. Many types of games and axes to choose from.

Nicely curated and organized shop with accessible prices.

However, the shop girl my group encountered was rude enough that we left without perusing the entire store.

Not sure if she was trying to be engaging or funny, but she butted in with snarky commentary to nearly everything we said to each other, even as we were leaving the store, chased out by her attitude.

I may give this shop another try, but I'll be sure to keep my mouth shut.

Overpriced and WAY TOO SALTY!  Ordered the small (3 scoops of protein - salmon, tuna, crab) with spicy shoyu marinade, cucumber, radish, scallions, brown rice.  $10 for a 4.5-5" diameter bowl (crab was $1 extra).  Traveled out of the way for a taste of home but will not be returning.  Makes for a good Instagram photo though~~

You guys! Why hadn't I been here before!? Travel to Florida and stay in the same hotel (which you really don't even have to leave the connected parking lot for!) After a very long and taxing work day, I wasn't really feeling like going out, so I ordered to go. I ordered Panang curry. Which is always my go to, to try anywhere. If I wanted to play it safe, I would get pad Thai, but nope! Well, the consistency of the curry was a little more watery than I'd like, and I wasn't liking the look, but the taste! The taste was there y'all!!! It was delicious!!! Also had some crab Rangoon's that had curry too!! Whaaat!? They were good, but all together with the meal I ordered, a bit curry'ed away. HAHAHA!!! The atmosphere was super cute!! The service, weeeelllllll, you don't normally go to a Thai restaurant because of the service. Unfortunate. But from my experience, true. Actually, quick story I'll tell that one of my employees told me from his visit... he ordered pad Thai and also tried to order two sushi rolls. The waitress told him that was too much food & she'd bring him one roll and he could order another one after if he wanted! OMG! Do you believe that? He said he ended up ordering another and he had to wait a while for it because the restaurant was busier now. That's cray! Sorry y'all! Had to  take off a star for that one! Let people order what they want! Why would you turn away money! Crazy talk!! Oh! Dessert!! I asked for a recommendation over the phone, but the girl was NOT interested in humoring my sweet tooth. I ordered some anyway and went with the little Thai doughnuts. They were doughnuts alright. Sweet and doughy. With some syrup on the side. Almost like little pancakes!! They did the desserts job. Anywho, I was satisfied with my dish, service was mediocre, but I'd still come back and enjoy some Thai!

If there is any place I have ever been to that should be on Triple D then this would definitely be near the top of my list. The place is truly a dive. That being said the service was great and the food was too. This used to only be a breakfast joint but they also do dinners now too. Parking is limited because this place is always packed. 

Try the green chile omelet for something a little different from the norm. They have a really good selection of traditional breakfasts and also include dishes with a Mexican flair. If it not a typical Tucson day where it is a ridiculously hot I think the patio is the place to sit. 

I will definitely be going back and after many visits to Tucson over the last 8 years I am glad I finally stumbled on this place.
Omg!  Great service. Great food. Probably the best bbq I've had in a long time. Prices are super reasonable. I'm so happy our joyride driver suggested this place. We will be back!!

I went here because a friend of mine kept raving about their fries and their fry sauce. The food is good and worth the price. The fry sauce is OK, but nothing super special. The beef they use is good and can tell it's not your normal burger. I think I spent $9 for a burger meal with bacon. They have shoestring fries just like Steak N Shake. As a matter of fact, they remind me a lot of them. So if you like SNS you will like Freddy's.
very good, very quick service, HOT cocktail sauce, great rib eye, huge portions, share the shrimp, huge wine selection .. a very nice experience .. worth the money ..

3rd time is the charm!!! Real sized ribs not mini ribs (Slopes bbq), well seasoned, not drowned in sauce (daddydz) AFFORDABLE!!!!!! plate only 12.95 unlike daddydz $20 and
slopesbbq $20, beef has super smokey beef flavor. Good service, great food, and AFFORDABLE don't feel like I got ripped off. Even the hushpuppies were good. Pickles were delicious and crisp, did not make my stomach hurt like (slopesbbq)

We are in the midst of perfect spring days where the sun is bright, the breeze is in full effect, and nights have limited mosquitoes. 

Tampa Riverwalk is a great place to experience the beauty of Tampa on the Hillsborough River. Family and friends along with your children and pets have access to this. There is a nice clean walk way with beautiful water views and scenery of different landmarks of Tampa including Straz Performing Arts, Glazer, Sono  Cafe, Curtis Hixon, and University of Tampa to name a few.

You can park your boat,  and take a walk. You can even rent a bike, and take a bike ride on the Riverwalk.

It is a great location too because some of the hotels have the Riverwalk as their view, or back. You can just walk in the back of the hotel to get there.

In my opinion, the Riverwalk is even better at night. You get to see the glow from the lights, and it is just is a serene, nice place to be. There are lots of benches too if you want to take a break from your walk.

I look forward to the Riverwalk getting even better and better as the time progresses.

We saw more species of animals here than in the SF Zoo. Walk from the main parking lot (where the Busch Clydesdales are) to the tram house - your first gift shop opportunity is right there.

Then onto the Jurassic Park tour - as the announcer jokingly stated. All kinds of rare breeds and not-so-rare to drive past. Big healthy grounds that are beautifully wild yet maintained...The fact that so many of the animals are reproducing suggests a healthy and happy environment for the animals.

You're dropped off at the main center starting with a petting zoo of pygmy goats. Bottles of goat formula for $1 each. Feed llamas, look at camels and monkeys (new baby!), guinea pigs and other little animals.

Also on the property... a tiny gift shop, a fastfood area to get bratwurst and the likes, Budweiser tasting bar with a 2-sample limit, a stable of horses - say hello to Boomer the donkey that wants to be a Clydesdale. Mini-musem with the family's horsing history.

Make sure to see the Clydesdales before leaving the parking lot. They're even bigger than you realize.
worst nail salon ever. sat for an hour waiting while they just talk to each other. does awful job and rude people. if u want an awful manicure this is the place

So good! I had the gyro salad and the lettuce and toppings were fresh and flavorful. Portions are HuGe! You definitely get your money's worth. A little hole in the wall type place with a mom and pop feel. I'll be back!

I honestly don't even know where to start. If you don't consider yourself a foodie, I garuntee you will be after your first few minutes walking through this place. To simply put it, the Reading Terminal Market is heaven. I'm surpised they don't have a Golden gate and angels at the entrance. There is every kind of cusine you can think of and it is all authentic and as fresh as can be. A few of the restaurants in there have been featured on food network tv shows. And many of the places are Zagat rated. For you sweets lovers, they have a whole aisle of just that and if you don't see what you're looking for on display, there's a few places that can make any dessert/ cake you body/ mind desires. This place is so amazing, I can't even say what my favorite restaurant is. There's just waaaay too many! To add to that, they also have amazing coffee, book stores, a nut stand, Amish stand, ice cream stands, cookie stands, an oyester bar, exotic grill chees stand, bee wax product stand, fresh bread stands, a few vegetable and seafood stands with unbeatable prices and products, just to name a few. They occasionally events/ shows around the food court which makes it almost too much to handle. Annnd difficult to navigate. Speaking of navigating, that's my only complaint about this place. It gets super, ridiculously, unbelievably crowded on the weekends. But that's only because it's clearly one of the best things that Philly has to offer. Simply put, if the Reading Terminal Market was the only place I could eat for the rest of my life and the next life, I would be perfectly ok with that. So do yourself a favor and treat your taste buds to total euphoric pleasure.
-You're welcome ;-)

Came here because a friend wanted to go. 

As soon as I walked in, the smell of nail polish/acrylic fumes hit us instantly. The floors were dirty, and if you wanted to pick a gel color, you had to choose a "regular nail polish color," and then they would match it to the real gel bottles on the other side of the salon. Why aren't we allowed to pick from the actual gel colors? 

I felt rushed and part of my nails weren't actually painted. The woman who was doing my nails started on another woman while I was almost done my gel manicure. 

I didn't want to go to this location, but only went because of a friend wanted to. My friend even said she was sorry for bringing me. 

Never again. Please clean the floors and pay attention to your customers. We spend our money for a little pampering and relaxation- we don't want to be rushed and hurried in a dirty environment.

Need new kitchen knives, shop Bertarelli.

Need your current kitchen knives sharpened, take them to Bertarelli. 

Need some new gadget for the kitchen, shop Bertarelli. My favorite gadget was battery powered pepper mill. It was so cool.

Customer Service is great.

Come
For happy hour and order your flight of 4 ciders to choose between the 20 some options.
Very interesting flavors.
Order a pizza from the food cart outside and play some games!
I love this cute place.  Very friendly atmosphere and the food is really good and comes out fast.  Ate breakfast there everyday and loved the strawberry kiwi tea.  Highly recommend this place.

I had the shrimp hot pot which I must say was very delicious. At $15 I did feel it was a little pricey considering there really wasn't that much to it. The flavor was great though. Service was average. I was shocked that the place was so busy in the middle of the week. So be prepared because there was a line forming around 7:30! I'd try it again, I saw some fish that other people ordered that looked intriguing as well!

Great customer service complements a good product. Excellent people, exquisite chicken and deliciously cooked eggplant. Great prices compared to other restaurants that get more hype. You must try this place. Great prices, great atmosphere and a uniquely flavorful fried chicken.

Wish I could update to zero stars. This place is a joke.

Had to cancel my credit card because it got stolen...I forgot to update them so boom. a late fee. I can accept that, they are a nickel and dime type of place so I expected nothing less. Next month's bill....still a late fee. I call, pissed off, since I had already given them my new CC number over the phone. Apparently all changes have to be made in person at the club & the girl taking my credit card number on the phone neglected to mention that. Awesome! Thanks a lot girl!

Whatever, I hope the $50 bucks was worth it for them. I cancelled (but still have to pay for three months). Stay far away from this place. Please.

This review is long overdue, but I wanted to share my love for this Vegan Junk food joint :)  We go to Blackbird often, and we love a few of the items on their menu, and we haven't tried anything that we don't like.  The tops are:

1.  Fungi Pizza (Absolutely Delicious!)
2.  Haymaker Pizza (Its a good substitute when you're craving a "meaty" supreme)
3.  French fries... so yummy!
4.  Chickpea parm...  like a chicken parm, but with a fried chickpea patty (Be careful, they are super hot when served...  I have burned the roof of my mouth a few times with these delicious items)
5.  Their cookies :)  They are baked in shop in Bethlehem (I think..) but brought in so they are fresh.  They are SO good...  I have to eat one every time we go.  

Their other sandwiches are okay, but I don't crave them, and I didn't care for the wings.  The texture was a bit off and they were over sauced.  There are some other places in town that make splendid wings (e.g. Fergies), and unfortunately, Blackbird did not stand up.  

Other items to comment on:

1. The food is  a bit pricey, but that is to be expected at most specialty food shops (and I'll happily pay a bit more to not have think about each ingredient in my food selection).  
2.  The atmosphere is very laid back.  We often get delivery so we can enjoy a more relaxed meal.  
3. Yes... They do deliver!  Even across town.  Their delivery is consistently quick.

Amazing place close to beautiful downtown. The staff (chris and Carlos) treated us like royalty and gave us gifts also the wine is very good and decently priced. We always stop by when we are in town! Great place!

These guys are fantastic. They in one visit determined the problem our dog was having that two other vets were not able to figure out in two months. Immediate treatment and she was on her way to getting better. Polite, professional, well organized. Great customer service. Very appreciated when you are stressed out over your dog being ill. We were impressed. Not the place for everyday care-this is the place you go to when your pet is having serious issues or you need someone who is more of a specialist then your everyday vet. Yes it costs more, because they are specialists. And you get what you pay for. I would certainly use this hospital again if the need arises.

The food is delicious and the prices are very reasonable. Great advertising lead to overwhelming support, which the restaurant is slightly struggling to keep up with. In no time, this place will be a community staple.
The best kept secret in Indy!  I went there today for the first time and fell in love!  The food is awesome, the portions absolutely huge ..definitely becoming my favorite breakfast place!

With apologies to the Starbucks crews near my house and work, Handlebar is my favorite coffee shop in Santa Barbara. 

For one, the indoor space is open and airy and my eyes dont feel like theyre scanning the interior for Waldo--it's not busy, just simple and clean. The outdoor patio is big, and might feel bigger than it is, but being in an old alleyway off Canon Perdido with a perfect view of the Presidio has it as a make-shift paseo and perfectly Santa Barbarian. 

And of course the product. The coldbrew is my favorite. It tastes like coffee without a bite (that is, it doesnt come with an acidic taste). I've had the mocha before which is also good on colder mornings and days. All of what they serve lacks that secret "burned water" ingredient of a lot of coffee chains. 

Staff isn't always the friendliest. Theyre polite, theyre professional (or try to be), so you're not going to get bubbly new bff's from your experience, but to be honest I'll take the trade-off of the space, the view, and the coldbrew.

The low reviews of Jim Russel's had me apprehensive. If you are looking for pristinely organized vinyl in gem condition, keep walking. The place is a dump. The stacks are disorganized chaos and yes, the peculiar smell. Although I appreciate a well organized store, once in a while diving into chaos for vinyl is quite thrilling--so I dove. 

I caught Jim Russell's at the tale end of the day but came away with some good jazz finds. It's definitely not the place to look for new vinyl and yes examine your purchases carefully. The abundance of 45s is pretty impressve. The prices were a steal in my opinion. I'd definitely give this place another go.

This place is amazing in every way. The sunset view from this restaurant is breathtaking. The service was tentative and impeccable. The food and drinks were some of the best I've had. I highly recommend the meat and cheese platter and the Ossco Busco here. In my opinion, Armani's is one of the nicest fine dining restaurants in the Tampa Bay area. And it may be on the expensive side but it is worth it because you'll get what you pay for.
I sat at the bar....excellent oysters and gumbo.  I had two dozen and a bowl as dinner washed down with a couple of ice cold beers.

Our family spent two weeks vacation in Florida. We rented twice with Dollars rental.  The first time was on 06/24/12 picked up at Orlando, Fl for one day and car returned back to Tampa, Int'l, Fl the next day. At the time of the Orlando office, I was offered optional insurance coverage, I told the agent to decline all, my AAA insurance card was accepted and everything went fine with the rental.  The big problem came from the 2nd rental at Tampa Int'l on 06/30/12.  We rent for 8 days and car return to Orlando, Int'l.  At the time, the lady agent tried her every effort to sell me and even pressure me on the optional insurance coverage which I had declined once from my last car rental.  It was additional of $26.99 per day X 8 days = $215.92.  I told her that our AAA insurance and American express card will cover the optional insurance and my last rental at Orlando was accepted my AAA card.  She told me that she didn't need the card. Then, I was told from her that Tampa is different than Orlando. I then told her that my insurance agent told me that it will cover and she began to say things can happen...if my rental car ended up in the auto shop, our AAA will not cover the cost of lost daily rental.  I told her that we will be staying in our timeshare resort, very safe and we will not drive out that much. However, she threatens me that it can happen because it was happened to her in a resort with her car and etc...After 25 minutes of all talks, I finally told her just declined everything and I need to get going.  In return, she answered okay & fine with very dismay voice and told me to sign in the box to agree my rental.  I then signed in a black box trusted the agent waived all optional insurance.  She printed the estimate invoice, inserted into the paper sleeve. By then, I was very tired, without checking my invoice and gone pick up my car. (I am a believer in "honest system".) During whole rental time, my wife was with me and listened to all whole conversations.  However, I would never think that the agent would add on the optional insurance to my rental after the long declined talks!!! I found out the extra charges until my car returned to Orlando, Int'l on 07/07/2012. My invoice came out $449.78 instead of $233.86.  My daily rental rate is only $17 dollar and the additional insurance was $26.99 per day?! I complained the wrong charges at the airport office, I told them the whole story and the answer we received was nothing that they can do, transaction was posted, it was rented from them and it's our responsibly to read thru all fine lines before signing!!  I was told to contact the corporate customer service department. 
My wife contacted them this morning, I was told that was my fault that I did not read all fine lines before signing and my agent have nothing to do with it.  But that's not true, she had the computer and all function keys, just like at McDonald's, I requested no mustard or cheese and the agent will able to key in all request.  In additional to my signing, the agent did not tell me the amount that I am signing off.  It' was the same way I signed from Orlando Dollar's.  My answer from dollar's corporate was that they are not McDonald's!!! 
I am extremely upset that Dollar's Tampa Int'l have such dishonest business practice and also allowing and backing their employee up to do that kind of things. I worked hard for every one of my dollars and each one does not come easy.  With this experience, I will stay away from Tampa, Florida and Dollar Rent A Car !!

I have been to Acadia a number of times and have enjoyed most everything they have to offer. They have a robust Happy Hour that runs from 5-8pm Tue - Fri with $5 food and $5 drinks.  Until $8pm !! Incredible deal for late working folks. 

My favorite cocktail is Le Petit Mort which has a rosemary infused vodka, gin, lemon juice, rosemary simple syrup and grapefruit juice, shaken and then strained into a glass with a blow-torch seared spear of fresh rosemary (such a dramatic sight for the whole bar to see). I want to try other cocktails, but always am drawn to Let Petit Mort. The Hurricane is also delicious. They have fresh beers on tap flown in direct from NOLA, so Acadia is the only place in Philly that serves Abita Amber Lager. Red and White wines are also on tap and served by the glass, 1/2 carafe or full carafe.

I love the Viet-Cajun Boil which is super flavorful as is, while my husband likes Burn Yo' House Down style, which is super hot. The shrimp Étouffée has deep flavors and the Creole Jambalaya is outstanding. I also enjoyed the Blackened Catfish with collard greens and mashed potatoes one evening. The remoulade sauce on the Shrimp Po Boy is classic tasty. While the roll is about 6", it was plenty for me as it is served with seasoned fries. The chicken wings are the best I've ever had, with deep, soulful Cajun flavors. 

I just went for brunch this past weekend and was not disappointed. Bottomless Mimosas with whatever juice you prefer for $18. All the classic lunch and dinner Acadia dishes and then some great new breakfast options. 

The beignets are a winner and they also serve chicory coffee.

Did I mention that there is Comedy Night on Wednesdays with no cover and you will find live music regularly? They also show Saints games on Sundays. 

This is a great little spot with beautiful decor and furnishings and very caring staff. Always a diverse crowd and always a great experience. Like a trip to New Orleans without the airfare.

Wide ranging draft beer menu with a slim selection of bottled brews.   They could enhance the overall beer selection a little by adding some more good local keg beer and by offering some more range on their bottles (both domestic and import). 

Food is typical pub fare, not bad but certainly not anything that's unique or special.  I tried the zinger tacos which consist of their hot wing breast pieces served in a soft taco shell, I thought it was a cool idea to make a wing taco, the result however was just OK, adding some guacamole and fresh salsa would have made them better.

The outer bar has a porch type atmosphere which can be fairly loud.
First time eating here and tried the 3 tacos combo. They were excellent and couldn't recommend them enough. Staff was very helpful and extremely nice. Will come back

Worst Chinese I've had in many years, unfortunately.  The meat was an impossible combination of both too greasy and too dry and desiccated.  Made me sick to my stomach upon leaving and left me disquieted the rest of the night.  I had some general Tso's chicken and some crab rangoons from the buffet.

SOOOO.    had  an  appointment  for  today 8-21-2019 between  8-9 am
NO  show  NO  call.  my  time  is  just  as  valuable  as  theirs.  Think  that   its  poor  business.
Walked in, no one was around. When someone did come out of the back room she was half dressed and claimed to be " trying on clothes." The entire experience was weird.

My wife and I were car shopping, stopped by, and had the falafel recommended by the friendly guy behind the counter. It was the best falafel I've had, and my had a heck of a calzone. Head in and support a really nice guy's business.

OMG! The sushi here is amazing and I have also discovered that i like hot saki, who knew? The food is delish and inexpensive and the employees were super nice and so funny they all seemed to get along very well with eachother which made a nice atmosphere to dine. When visiting Reno i will be back.
I'm so glad to have Napoli in St Charles!!! Great food and our service was great! Love the atmosphere!!
Really great Rueben and staff were excellent! Would definitely eat here again if I lived in New Orleans.

Not fully sold on any butcher shops, in general, my first purchase was 2.5 lbs boneless lamb stew meat, 2.5 lbs corned beef and 2 lbs reg ground beef. The meats were so flavorful, I decided that I would buy a full week's worth of meats.  Every meal this past week has been very good.  I can tell these meats are of better quality and much better handling than what I was buying at the grocery stores.  I still buy my seafood from the grocery store, as they don't have a very large selection of fish here.  The pricing on beef and pork products are comparable to those found in grocery stores, but I find the price of their poultry to be on the high side.  However, the quality of their boneless/skinless chicken breasts cannot compare to the grocery stores.  I wish they sold cage free eggs.  Did you know that eggs with a yellow or light orange yoke come from unhealthy chickens - resulting in their eggs being unhealthy, too?  Also, the round shapes of these colored yokes are not what a healthy egg yoke looks like.  Eggs from a healthy chicken are actually oval deep orange.  Such eggs will be very healthy and nutritious, unlike the yellow or light orange yoked ones we have been getting pretty much all of our lives.  I mentioned this about eggs, because if this company is able to provide us with such quality meats at reasonable prices, I figure if they sold eggs, as well, they would be of a very high quality, with oval dark orange yokes - at a reasonable price.   If you haven't tried any of their meats, I highly recommend you do and start buying your meats from them.  You won't be disappointed!

Love this place! Great location. Cool atmosphere. Very friendly, courteous and accommodating staff. Normal bumps and learning curve of the first couple weeks of opening but nothing offensive. I expect that in no time they'll be up to speed and just as popular as their Brentwood location.

UPDATE:  


OK!  So, since my initial review, my girlfriend and I have made HIS AND HERS our weekly go to spot while I am in Philadelphia.  And they just do not disappoint.  We love the environment, the people are so freakn awesome and we finally tried the food on a couple of different occasions.  I would recommend the Salmon or the Brozino (which I learned is a fish from Turkey).  They both were just delicious.  My girlfriend had lamb chops. She was mad I don't eat meat because she really wanted me to try them.  She said they were to die for.  You can say, I am SOLD on this place.  When I am back in Philly, I will definitely be back at His and Hers!  Oh and based on another review from Yelp, I tried the Baklava... Just DO IT! ;)

So Steven Starr kinda-sorta redid the bar at the back of the old Midtown 2 Diner and now it's the "Ranstead Room" - a pricey , dimly-lit speakeasy with fresh ingredients and $12 drinks.

Think Candied Ginger and Granny Smith Apples.

Fun.

Still got the old tufted red booths - just polished up a bit with the cracks repaired.

Grab dinner at El Rey and then walk ALL THE WAY AROUND (Darn it, just open the door!) to Ranstead.

Oh - and they don't even open until 7 PM - so NO happy hour here.

After much eating in N'awlins. not all of it very good, Rum House was an amazing surprise. Everything was deeelish and not outrageously touristy priced either. The avacado mango dip appetizer was an awesome starter.  The margaritas were smooth with plenty of alcohol. The damn good nachos were DAMN GOOD looking.  The meal and service were terrific as well. Highly recommend! Go and enjoy

Great food!! Staff super friendly and really great vibes 100% recommend if you want to eat some good food and have some great drinks with a beautiful view this is the place i been here about 3 times and i will definitely keep coming back.

The food quality is amazing. We're a party of four traveling to Philly on New Year's Day and we're so glad we had our first dinner of 2021 here. The charred octopus is a bit bitter but otherwise we like everything we ordered. The fish fillet is especially impressive, it's worth coming again for.

Honestly the best Vietnamese in Tampa,Iv been coming here since I moved to FL when they were still located on Dale Mabry.
