Even in San Diego were majority of the people are asian...Pho quyen takes number 1

I go every week !

Searched out this spot for breakfast today. Sounded great, so off I went with my wife and daughter. Sadly, they were closed today. Best to call ahead if you are going there. Love the outside environment, except it was pouring rain, off to Cake we went. Delicious!

Owners/ employees are super rude and cussed me out when I entered their "closed" store (THE DOOR WAS OPEN!) and I said that I didn't know they were closed hence the door was open; then they preceded to cuss me out and saying very insulting things to me. -100000/5 stars for me.

Being from out of town, I walked up to the counter and was amazed at the selection of items available!  I then simply asked what he suggested... he suggested the cheese steak.  Turned out to be a good choice!  The sandwich was a little greasy, but very, very good!
Amazing beers. Haven't had a beer that hasn't surprised me.  Only wish is that they would continue to grow the food menu. Cannot wait to try the outside bar area this summer!
Food and service was amazing! I tried the rice and peas, shredded beef and beef ribs and it was delicious. Will definitely be going back.

I really appreciate their late hours and they never seem to be too busy.  The staff has always been very friendly and helpful.  When I am in South Tampa, this is the post office I will drive a little out of my way to get to.  There is ample designated parking, but you have to be patient with the airport's weird layout and traffic light patterns coming out of the lot.

This restaurant was absolutely fabulous as far as service and cleanliness is concerned. The hosted was engaging and attentive. Even though it was a busy day, we had a table earlier than she promised. The waitress was great on suggestions. The food took a while to get to the table, but this is expected due to business levels.. bathrooms cleanest I've seen in all of New Orleans. My boyfriend loved the memorabilia and beer menu. Happy new year to the Mannings and bravo on such a great experience.

The Row was a good choice for lunch.  Our server, whose name I wish I remembered, was fantastic, especially when I need to sample several beers before choosing.  I eventually chose a Yazoo, but forget which one--it was great though.

We started with the fried pickles, which I never like, but these were super tasty, and as a non-pickle eater, I would eat these again.  I ordered the Nashville hot chicken with a spicy corn cake and bacon mac and cheese.  The chicken was good--I ordered a heat level of hot, which was spicy, but not overly so.  However, the bacon mac and cheese was perfect, with the right amount of bacon and well-cooked macaroni. My sister liked her veggie burger (and I liked her fries) and our friends enjoyed their chicken-fried chicken.

The whole vibe of The Row is friendly and welcoming, and it's definitely music-themed, which I loved.

Terrific service- Jean is interested in forming a relationship with you- not a one time transaction, and it shows. She goes in depth into all the details and explains every part of the process. Was a joy talking to her- a true people person who puts you at ease. Not only did she help me with my taxes, but she put me in touch with people who would be able to help me with my financial goes. She's been a part of the community for a long time and makes an effort to network within it- this is helpful when you're new to the area and looking for people to talk to!

We ordered take out twice and both times they messed up. 1st time we got a side of beans, potato salad, brisket, and pulled pork. They forgot the pulled pork... not a big deal as the food was so good. I even gave them a glowing review below. 

Next time we ordered, we got the same thing minus the pulled pork. Because of the previous mishap they offered to refund us for the pulled pork which was great. However... instead of brisket we got pulled pork plus they threw in another pound of pulled pork for the previous inconvenience. When we called back to let them know we got the wrong order and we were told sorry but nothing we can do. Then we asked about the price difference. They told us pulled pork is the same price as the brisket. It is not. There's a $5 difference. We asked for a call from the owner and nothing. Really unfortunate
Would recommend the seafood sampler. I had the Louisiana BBQ shrimp which was good but my friend's seafood sampler looked better. Service was good also. Would recommend this restaurant.

Cool vibe, but could be more. I believe this place is riding the hype wave. The place has a good layout and lots to offer, but the details are ignored. The food, drinks, and service were OK, but could have been better. The fried chicken plate I got was a small serving for the price I paid. The cheese plate had a nice selection of cheeses, but was short on crackers and not well proportioned together. The kitchen is like  fish tank on display for the patrons. There are yard games like corn hole in the restaurant which is novel, but probably not the optimal way to cover the cost of such a large space. The beer selection was quirky and novel, but not great for the distribution available in the Tucson market. The service was good, but our server wasn't always available and it wasn't clear who to order from. I'm cheering for this place, but a lot of details to work out.

I don't know where to even begin. What a trip!!! My wife and I used Italy with Bella for planning out our 5 year wedding anniversary trip and they did not disappoint! We wanted that small town old world Italy feel and we got it! Sure we saw Rome and Venice which was great but we wanted to also hit the old fashion quaint little towns  nestled in the hills. Anthony and Denise made it happen!  Not only were they a pleasure to work with, but an absolute blast! Such a fun couple. Every step of the planning and prep work was exciting and not overwhelming in anyway. They were actually excited for us and helped us dream about what the best trip for us would look like. They know their stuff and are very well versed when it comes to travel and all things Italy. Every air bnb location was perfect, every restaurant they recommended was delicious (seriously, there was not one bad meal)  and every museum, cathedral, and even scenic view was spectacular!  Italy with Bella certainly under promised and over delivered with their recommendations, travel tips and assistance in planning every step of the way. They even were available by phone at anytime while we were over there to answer questions, help when we got lost and recommend back up plans if weather was a factor (which it was one day). I can't praise them enough. I do not recommend using anyone else if you are planning a trip to the beautiful country of Italy. They are WORLD CLASS.

My wife and I come to this place tucked away next to Brinton Lake Shopping Center on Saturday or Sunday morning for breakfast. 
The inside is bright and inviting.  Upon approaching the counter to order, there is a window case that displays the bakery items for that day.  Though I've never had one, they have some intruiging flavors and look delicious.  I usually opt for a sandwhich, however.
The staff are truly top notch.  They are very friendly, make good suggestions, and offer to bring your food out to your table.  They are constantly out in the dining area to keep the place clean.
My usual food items are the Sunrise egg and cheese breakfast sandwich on an everything bagel, or the hound dog, which is chunky peanut butter, banana, cinnamon, and honey on toasted sourdough bread.  I also really enjoy the Nutella Macchiato, both hot and iced.  I've also tried the Kona Mona Frappe, which my wife had me finished as she wasn't a fan.  More for me.  They also offer a pickle with your sandwich, which we will always take them up on!
As mentioned, it is a dog themed cafe, and there are rotating pictures of dogs on a video screen which brings a level of charm.
There is also outdoor seating which is great on a nice day.
I recommend PureBread to friends in the area, and we will continue to eat here in the future!

Moved to Brandon recently from st Pete so I was excited that they had a capital tacos here ... really disappointed with as much as they charge my food was cold ! And we were the only ones here so it wasn't as if they were busy. I will be taking the drive to st Pete going forward it will be worth the drive hot food
Pricing is usually good...unfortunately items are out of stock a lot of times.  I typically go to Safeway but to save time I'll shop small items at this store...

Been meaning to try this and since we were in the area, stopped in. Due to some bad reviews, I was hesitant. Glad we stopped. The Cuban sandwich was very good and large so although $12.99 may seem expensive, my mother and I split it. My son loved the pineapple burger. Black beans were good and so were the fries. Nice friendly waitress. Will be back
Very pricey, but the food is good.  Bring a fat wallet or a non-limited credit card!
Go here in a regular basis but sometimes the service is off. One night the server start very friendly and finished with a hurry attitude and became a little rude. But loved 1905 salad.

I've been to this nail salon many times and have always had great experiences. However, yesterday was the worst experience ever. I got my mani pedi for a wedding this weekend. My pedicure was great BUT the nail technician painted my toes the WRONG color. I thought they looked odd but did not notice that my toes and nails do not even match until this morning. In addition to this, during my manicure, the nail technician did not stay off his phone!!!! Every few minutes he stopped doing my nails to text or answer phone calls or to check the schedule. I sat there waiting for so long and felt like I was being completely ignored. It was horrible customer service and made me feel unappreciated. On top of it all, because my nail technician took SO LONG, the rest of my group had to leave me and I had to miss my brow waxing appointment. Long story short, this was such a subpar experience. I'm so disappointed and the kicker is that my mani-pedi doesn't even match.

Beautiful space with excellent instructors ( of which I am one so this review may be biased :) ). Group class size is small max of four people but still reasonably priced. Mat classes of max 8 people with lots of private and duets available.

For starters, they ran out of food.
6pm and their main menu item was gone. Second choice was the 10 ounce ribeye for $18. It was hard as leather. Definitely Not Fresh. I ate what I could not wanting to embarrass my family who was taking me out for Father's Day. It was the worse steak I've ever had... and I eat a lot of steaks.
You can get a better steak at Waffle House, which is sad. I don't usually give reviews, but this was so bad and dissapointing I have to say something so you don't make the same mistake. Service was good... but don't get their low end ribeye and ask first what food is still left from their menu specials.

Cheddars is pure and simply chain dining at it' absolute worst. As uninspiring as it is tasteless about the only thing this eatery has going for it it's cheap pricing...of course as the old adage says, you get what you pay for. The decor is campy and spartan, but not in an amusing way as you might find at an over the top restaurant like hooters, instead this appears to be the restaurant that Walmart decorated. Greatly akin to the bland and vanilla accouterments the menu is equally distasteful offering all the expected and overused American regulars from cheeseburgers to cheese fries, but with such lack of inspiration, seasoning or taste as to make the McDonald's Angus burger seem upscale and gourmet. If you like eating flavored cardboard this is your place, if not....steer clear and enjoy any number of countless other quality restaurants in and around the area.

My significant other and her daughter's all get their nails done here.  They're really awesome.  They keep their appointment times on-track (I know, because I'm the driver in all of these instances,) and they do a really nice job on their nails (I can also testify to that because my significant other will scratch my back!)  But more importantly, they're experts in their craft at OP Nail, including the decorative art they'll add to their client's fingers/toes.  Doesn't matter the occasion...the girls always come out of there with whatever holiday adornments are coming up on the calendar!
The price is VERY reasonable as well (again, I know from paying at times!)  OH, and they have gift certificates as well that "Santa" can deliver on Christmas.  I'm sure the Easter Bunny will put them in baskets as well.  The gift certificates can be purchased year-round.  
The staff is very friendly there, and it doesn't have an over-powering smell of chemicals (really nice!)  I hope they never figure out that I know enough Vietnamese language to get by...but I can testify that they don't talk trash about their clients! :)

I ran into the review for Bilenky Cycle Works and decided I needed to add another review myself.

Some time back, I commissioned Stephen to build my wife and I our dream tandem. We talked on the phone, via email, shared concepts and we finally came to agreement on the details and I paid a down-payment for him to get started.

I had very specific items I wanted to use for components and boxed them up and sent them away to BCW - including wheels built by Peter Jon White.

A month or two later, I got a message from Stephen stating that they have used up my deposit funds and needed additional money to continue - I obliged he charged my credit card again.

A month or two later, I again received a message from Stephen asking for more money as he once again has gone through the funds I had sent. This time I asked for status on the build - he said that they were still working and he had trouble with the plating, but he would catch up shortly and be back on track. He ended up charging my card again.

A month or two later, I again received a message asking for more money. This time I had asked for pictures of the progress he has made - he couldn't provide any.

Frustrated already, I demanded to see something he has done to make me feel comfortable with the build process. He then finally admitted that he had not made any progress on the build, but he needed money to keep his shop open.

I am now furious with Stephen and decide to move on and get my money back as there was no telling how long it would be before I receive our tandem. I ask for my money back - he replies that he doesn't have it to give to me.

OK - now I'm beside myself with anger. Not only do I not have our tandem after more than 6 months waiting, but he is telling me I cannot get my money back either.

I then remembered that payment was always made by my credit card. I tell Stephen that I will file a claim with my CC company and get my money back that way. He asks that I do not do that, that I should just wait until he has more money to reimburse me.

No way am I going to trust this guy any longer, and I also am way behind on my custom tandem build. I decide to file the claim anyhow and get my money back from them that way.

I can only imagine what his issues are, but I wouldn't trust this guy considering my experience and lies from Stephen.

Oh, in the end, I did get my parts back - I was surprised as I thought they were long gone.

The food has been good in the past. I frequently go to J's since it is by my job, however the last couple of trips have not been that Great.  I  usually  order the  Crawfish  Etoufee  over  Jambalaya and  Drunken  Chicken  .  Now  I  find  myself  searching  for the  crawfish and  only  3-4  slices  of  Andouille sausage .  Yesterday 8/17/14  I  was told  the  Crawfish  Etoufee  now  goes over  white  rice , when  that  had  not  been  the  case,  and there  was  additional  charge for the  Jambalaya.   Needless to say I'm disappointed.  I  guess  I  have  find  another  Cajun  Restaurant to  frequent

I've lowered my rating because recently they've been leaving small items off of my take away orders - 90% of the time I have a soup missing and it's not worth going back for.

Also noticed the spicy crunchy tuna has a lot less tuna than it use to.  A

Cute.
Smells great.
Tastes good.
Just like me!

J/k. I kid, I kid.
I stopped in while walking around downtown Franklin with friends, waiting for our dinner reservation time to roll around. A couple folks in our group were really excited to check out this spice shop, so we all went along inside.
It did indeed smell amazing.
You can buy different amounts, of your choice, of the flavored salts, rubs, dip mixes, and various other spices. Each offering has a small sprinkle bottle next to it for smell and taste tests. The truffle sea salt...is to die for! (as is the cost of it...it gutted me to have to leave without buying some, but it wasn't in my budget for the trip....)
This place is great and I wish there was one in my hometown....but, it looks like you can order online. So...my budget may remain in jeopardy! But my food will be heckin' tasty!

To start on a positive note, my waitress Karen was fantastic! Super charismatic and helpful! The fries and sauces were very yummy. However, I ordered the steak and fries, and requested it as medium well... it was medium rare. Then, I sent it back. When it came back, it was very unevenly cooked. Parts were still medium rare well while others were medium well. See pics. I sent it back again. When I got it back, the outside was burnt and it was actually a very fatty piece so I ended up not eating it all. For the trouble, my friend and I were treated with free dessert and the steak was taken off 100%.

I was pleasantly surprised by this small zoo.  It was easy to cover in a few hours and there was a great variety of animals.  I saw an anteater for the first time in my life!  This is definitely a place to recommend and return to.

I scheduled a balayage and a hair cut and when I was about five minutes away, I get a call that the stylist I book is not available. I was placed with Evan, who was supposed to be great with balayage and thin fine hair. I did not get a balayage nor is the color even much lighter. Almost looks like an all over lightening AND it's ash, which will turn green on me, even tho I asked for whiter balayage. The cut is horrific. I lost my base length and the layers are so choppy and uneven. I made sure to state everything I wanted and spoke up about having a wedding four months away. I'm so so so upset and disappointed. I got charged for the "balayage" and the salon was going to rebook me with the same stylist for a fix... no thanks.

Just darn good! Priced well too. Quick service and friendly people, including the patrons. The exterior definitely did not represent the experience. Will definitely visit again, and you should stop in sometime too!

Location, location, location.... 

This place has a great location. It's on Canal Street, so it's easy to drive up to and park your car (if you're driving).... and yet, it's just a few short steps away from where all the action is. 

Check-in was easy. They have a dedicated SPG Plat/Gold desk, however no one was attending when I checked-in at 9:45pm. 

As an SPG Platinum, I was upgraded to an Executive Suite. It basically was like the size or probably two regular hotel rooms there. But it was nice... there was a wet bar, refrigerator, separate bedroom ... nice living area with sofa and the windows all had blinds that opened up. My room had a view looking south Canal Street... so I could see Harrah's Casino and the river in the background. The sunrise over the river was beautiful!

The staff was extremely friendly.... especially the bell man, the valet guys, and the waitstaff at Roux Bistro. Speaking of, breakfast at Roux Bistro was very good. 

I had NO issues whatsoever with the elevators. They must have fixed since a previous poster had mentioned comments. It was a different elevator system than I've ever seen... people were confused. Basically you type the floor number you want to go and it would reply back the elevator letter to jump in. It worked though... and it was fast. I never waiting longer than 30 seconds for an elevator. 

All in all, a good stay. Was here for work. Next time when I visit with my husband I think we'll try the W French Quarter. 

Oh, and I had an awesome AAA rate. :) :)

I went here last summer...it's a pretty neat old building. They have a deck overlooking the Katy trail which is really nice. The menu was impressive...which lead me to think I was in for something amazing.   I ordered the pulled pork sandwich, cole slaw and beans.  The sides were good..the pork sandwich was  dry and chewy...not that great to be honest...maybe it sat too long on the grill to....in any case this was the main part of my meal so it was a disappointment.  There are better places in St. Charles for barbecue.

Customer service appears to be lacking. When calling into the office, we were transferred to a "hold line" and after an extended period the calls are cut off. When we looked for an email address or form on their site, the only option is if the person is already a patient, and has a patient number.

They must have had growing pains because this is the best place in Edmonton to get a pedi/mani! $40 for both! 

I've been coming here once a month for nearly a year now and I've always had a great experience. The husband and wife that run this place are the most adorable couple and always give the best service. 

This is a hidden gem in the west end!

Nothing to write home about

We had been meaning to try Benchmark for some time and are big fans of Brophy Brothers as well as On the Alley. While I like the "industrial" decor it does make for a "cold" and noisy environment. In addition, there are not ample heaters on patio for a cold evening. The service started out okay but went down as the evening went on. Food was okay. Fish and chips were very good but veggie sandwich as well as fried chicken sandwich just okay. Prices were fair but most likely won't be a place I will go back.

What a great burger! I have been wanting to try these guys out and I am glad I did! There is plenty of competition for these guys and they have my vote. TASTY burgers!!! QUALITY PRODUCT!! Casual and friendly staff with a clean ambiance makes for a very pleasant experience. I'll be back

Cute little restaurant where Haley's used to be, and it's a nice place to go for lunch. The sandwiches are really good, and they serve them with "Italian chips," which look kind of like pita chips but are seasoned very nicely. Service was pretty quick too. Prices are fairly reasonable for lunch. I'll probably be back in the future!

Excellent exhibit with great visuals and displays. But the best part is the knowledgeable and enthusiastic docents. I spoke with Will, a Vietnam veteran and military historian, for an hour. It was a masters course in WWII Air Force history. Great visit!!

Okay sorry I really wanted to like this place,  I drove by it several times and fell in love with the old stone building and hanging lights outside.  I was hoping for the same type of decor inside.  I walked in and BAM! its just another pizza place, with the old time table cloth, plain white walls and the initial feeling was unclean.  I had a piece of Sicilian pizza and my friend had a piece of buffalo chicken pizza.  The crust to the Sicilian was lite but the cheese and the sauce were nothing to write home about.  the chicken pizza had an attractive swirl of buffalo sauce but it was not enough and it lacked chicken.  Curious about the sauce I ordered   mozzarella sticks with sauce.  The sticks did not taste fresh and the sauce had no flavoring.  I was not impressed.  I was just expecting more from a restaurant in Newtown.  I must say though the young adults working there are very nice and professional and the service was excellent.  I will not be returning.

This used to be a favorite for lunch.  Over time, the food quality seems to have suffered, and it also seems less clean than it was.  

Competition for Mexican food is tough -- there are half-dozen places within 2 miles of this place that are better.

Been here a few times and was always pretty good ..came in for dinner last night and I won't be back ..nothing had much flavor at all my gnocchis were barely Luke warm the bread was cold .. my gf got clams that were very bland .. my tomato soup was Luke warm at best ..just not a good experience
First visit was outstanding. Dinner, Service and Beer/Wine were excellent. I would highly recommend their pulled pork sandwich on Paninni Bread. Homemade English Pudding was verg good.
Love this place! One of Tucson's great day trips for people who live in town and visitor's from out of town!

Since I haven't had the time to wash my car (for a while now) I've been meaning to get my car washed.  One day, while at the Tucson Mall,  I randomly decided to start looking for a car wash place and it seems like everyone in Tucson has bad reviews - except this place.  So I stopped by and unfortunately they were closing but the gentlemen there, Gabriel, was very nice, apologized profusely (for what I don't know) and told me to follow up with him the next day.  I was so impressed by Gabriel that I called to schedule not a wash but a DETAIL wash (my 1st lol) on my Tahoe.  I dropped it off one morning (you don't have to but for simplicity I did) and picked it up after work.  Man, these guys are awesome... they washed the outand inside, shampooed the interior,  did a really nice job in the rims, took off some stupid decals I couldn't, and made it look like new.  I texted my family to tell them it was as if I'd just bought it again.  Lastly, the price wasn't bad (140), I'd called around and some guys were asking from 2-280 for the same work.  There's a reason Super Shine has the best reviews, I highly recommend them.

This is an excellent restaurant! The pizza is as good as Treno!!! Which is a big deal. All the food was very well priced at Bricco also. Unlike Treno who have gradually raise their prices over the years i.e. Appetizer meatballs went from $4 to $8 (which is crazy) anyway back top Bricco, It's BYOB which means you can save a lot of money. I have tried several pizzas and dishes at Bricco and they have been very good. Very fresh ingredients are used. Only 1 problem with Bricco is something that they cannot help is the noise. It gets pretty noisy in there also it gets hot sometimes also. I wish they delivered!!!! I would have it every night.This place is going to do really well!

I hadn't been to this location in a while. I went this afternoon for lunch, and while the pizza is still delicious, the service was pretty appalling. The employees were all nice to customers, but they all acted unprofessional with each other. They kept yelling at each other about not doing things or who's job it was to do something. In turn, the service was INCREDIBLY slow. We had to wait 20 minutes in line. This wasn't during the lunch rush- I've been here when the line is insane and there's nowhere to sit, and the line moves super quick. There were like 4 people in line in front of me, and it took them painfully long to make the pizzas. Also, when I stood at the cash register, the cashier was totally oblivious and another employee yelled at them to help me, but instead he just talked back to her before finally turning to help me. It was so awkward. I love the pizza, but I don't enjoy spending my lunch standing in an abysmally slow line while employees bicker.
Good spot to eat at ran into a small problem but the manager fixed it and I enjoyed my dinner

I bought a purple shampoo, toner and developer and after using the shampoo my hair roots were so rough I couldn't comb my hair without using a lot of leave in conditioner.  I was afraid to use the toner and developer after reading reviews online of how easy it is to mess up my hair so I tried returning both.  

The store only gives you a bag if you pay for it so I lost my receipt.  The girl who helped me 2 days ago recognized me and I had the same credit card that I bought it with, but they will only give store credit unless you have the receipt.  

After getting such bad advice from her about that purple shampoo removing the brassy yellow from my hair (which it didn't do) I don't trust the store and didn't want the store credit.  Waste of $15 for the shampoo.  No one wants their long hair to break at the root of be so rough that you can't comb it!  

Told her I would rather throw it away then have store credit!  I opened the bottle and dumped it in the outside trash can while she watched. 

I will never come back!

First visit to Circles in Collingswood with friends was good.  To be honest I expected a little more. My review is actually 3.5 stars losing a half point for slow service.

Started off by waiting 20 minutes to get a server... not a good beginning when hungry ;)

Had fried tofu, steamed dumplings and crab rangoon as apps.   The rangoon was stellar!

For the meal had pad thai duck.  They got the spice right but the duck was overcooked and dry.  My wife had the pad thai crab which honestly tasted a bit fishy (more than you would expect as if canned crab claw was used.

Also the desert menu was very lacking in choices as well as imagination. So we passed.

I wish I could write more but there was nothing terrible or exceptional about this place so will not likely return.

For Thai and Thai fusion there are a lot of great choices so will look elsewhere.
Solid bbq, delicious sides. Been there once, going to try again sometime soon ish. Not much in terms of drinks, tea, soda, no beer or anything that I could see.

We went for restaurant week and paid $35 each. I believe it's usually around $70. It's completely worth it for restaurant week! There's a green and red token card that you can flip to indicate if you're ready for more meat or not. They come around with a variety of different meats that they slice for you. The salad bar wasn't that special. There was just a lot of cheese spreads. They also give you some side dishes. My favorite was the mash potatoes.

We had a great time on this tour. The tour guide, Denise, had lots of interesting stories. Even if you don't believe in witches, ghosts, and vampires, this tour is entertaining and you will learn some interesting facts about New Orleans.

Came after a Pelicans game looking for a good burger. One of our group was wearing a sleeveless jersey and was refused seating even on the outside patio. Will take business elsewhere for a "bar food" type of establishment.

I know the old timers and locals really seem to like it here but I can only give a place so many chances to disappoint me before I decide not to return. Besides making an overly stiff drink and great onion rings the rest of the food just seems to be average and even sub par at times. The staff is friendly enough but it's not enough to draw me back when I'm hungry.

Had a great time on this tour! We took the cemetery tour in mid January 2012.

George was a great tour guide! Very knowledgeable, interesting, and entertaining. Just a little soft spoken. Wish he would have projected more.

Thought about just doing the walk through the cemetery on our own- but I'm glad we took a tour because we learned about the burial rituals, architecture of the city, history, and facts about Marie Laveau.
After the cemetery portion, we took a break at the visitor's center where we were able to grab a drink and have a bathroom break which was nice.
George then pointed out on a map the geography of New Orleans and talked a little about Katrina, which was a nice addition to the tour.

I was a little disappointed with the voodoo portion. George talked a little at the visitors center about voodoo, and warned us that we we going to Priestess Miriam's shop ( a voodoo priestess), and that sometimes she speaks about voodoo, and other times she is way off topic, and can ramble on and on about whatever. He was right! A lovely woman- but  a bit of a wacko.. she spoke nothing about voodoo. She went on and on about how far our country has come, a funeral she went to in another city, and where everyone was from, but nothing about voodoo. We did get to see her "office" where she does readings and that was pretty cool I guess. She was sweet.. but dang! I wanted some voodoo info!

All in all- nice tour. Glad we did it.

As a visitor to Nashville, I was hoping to get some delicious Southern chicken, and Hattie B's did not disappoint. The line is super long, but the hot chicken was bomb and the sides were solid too. Definitely would recommend going to this place.

Drinks upstairs is nice esp when it's nice out.  From the outside, it doesn't look like a famous restaurant or anything fancy.  I thought it was a diner!  But the food is decent but the drinks are pretty bad and overpriced.  It's an interesting decor though.

Dr. Waring and his entire team at Damonte Ranch dental care are beyond amazing! Their office is impeccable and filled with state of the art equipment and instruments. They truly care about their patients and make you feel like family. If you care about your teeth and oral health as much as I do, then do yourself a huge favor and choose them for your entire family! I promise it'll be the best decision you've ever made for your mouth. I'm probably the pickiest person on this planet, so if I recommend them, you know they're the BEST!

It's been over two years since my initial review and I've recently been back a couple times so an update is due. For whatever reason, I still don't love it here. All the pieces seem to be there, yet it just seems to fall short. I've dined a couple times before a show at Powell and made sure to get there plenty early based on other reviewers bad service experiences. I never had any major issues. Both times our server was friendly and the food came out very quickly. There was a small wait for the bill and once the server forgot to take off our coupon, but other than that it was fine.

I almost always order grilled cheese when it's on the menu, so I made sure to try the Royal Grille - white cheddar and mozzarella with apple slices. I really only have one demand when I order a grilled cheese and that's that the cheese be thoroughly melted and hot when delivered. This one wasn't. The cheese looked like it was melted at one point, but sat in the kitchen too long and hardened up again. I realize it's hard when there are four other entrees, but a grilled cheese is really time sensitive so please get it to the table asap.

The sandwiches come with a choice of salad or chips and both the St. Louis City salad and Stutz salad are both good. The STL City salad tastes exactly like the Pasta House salad. The Stutz is a little more inventive with goat cheese and an interesting dressing.

The best thing I've tried on the menu is the Blackhawk. This is something I would never order, but my husband got it and I tried it and it was delicious. The rolls were super soft and the spread of olive oil, basil, garlic, and goat cheese was a perfect complement.

The Focaccia Florentine was a let down. It's a very small piece of focaccia covered in basically spinach artichoke dip topped with two tomato slices.

On to dessert. It might be a little unfair to rate dessert since I'm not a huge ice cream person and much prefer cakes, pies, tarts, etc., but oh well. I've only ordered the pineapple inside out cake since it's only one of two items on the menu that isn't all ice cream. It is really good. I love their whipped cream and carmel sauce. Very good.

So basically the food is OK and I wouldn't go here just for the ice cream. It is a really awesome idea for a restaurant/soda fountain and I'm glad it's here, it's just not one of my favorites.

We used to come here a lot about 15 years ago, but I feel that the food quality has slipped and the interior is very dated and needs an update.  The bread rolls, however, are outstanding.  Last time we went there was a piece of plastic (from the bag or something) that was in with the fried calamari.  We were eating at the bar and the bartender didn't seem to care.

Worth the wait if there is a line...but this is one of my favorite places to eat in New Orleans. Everything on the menu is delicious, especially the burgers. Breakfast food is also amazing. Atmosphere is fun.

BRICS is by far my favorite ice cream spot in Indianapolis. Their portions are very generous, and they have tons of great flavors you wouldn't find just anywhere. My personal favorite is Chocolate Malt Supreme. Another great thing about BRICS is that they let you split up your servings, even for one scoop! I have a friend who gets one scoop, or even the smaller "bric-let" split between two flavors. The staff are very accommodating.

There's outdoor and indoor seating, so it is a perfect stop year round. As an added plus, there are conversation cards on the tables which make for hilarious (and heartfelt!) conversation between new pals or longtime friends.

Not ready to admit summer is over? Juno is the answer! They've started to transition some of their decor and cocktails to welcome a fall-feeling, but the overall vibe is the perfect outdoor summer bar. 

The flavors of the Elder Cider were perfect for the transition into fall - warm spices reminiscent of this time of year and a floral note, so you don't cave to the fall flavors too quickly! Nachos are my guilty pleasure and there are 3 things that I look for in good nachos - thick, crispy chips that don't get overly soggy, good distribution of toppings, and flavor - these nachos hit all the marks! The only thing that would have made them better would be a drizzle of cheese sauce, because I admittedly like both melted cheese and cheese sauce on my nachos. The pork carnitas tacos were juicy and they did not skimp on the filling. Only downside is a single layer of the tortillas, which can lead to tacos that fall apart easily. 

While we enjoyed our time overall, at 6pm on a Thursday, they did have 2 kicked kegs from the short draft list offered, which was a little frustrating for the beer drinkers in our group. 

Pro tips: reservations are highly recommended - don't be late! You'll get a $10 fee tacked onto your resy. Have a crew of 4+? The Beerbarrow is the perfect solution to quench your thirst - 12 Miller High Life's and a bottle of infused tequila will be rolled out to your table. For $60 - this seems worth it, as drinks can add up quickly!

Just a disclaimer I'm giving 1 star due to experience not the quality of the restaurant. 
My boyfriend and I love coming her for breakfast on our days off together and have been going consistently since I moved to Idaho in September. This morning we decided to stop by for breakfast and we're seated right away as always. The waitress (who seemed new) was and older woman who was lovely initially. Took our drink orders and food orders right away. Then things got interesting, when she came back to check on us before our food arrived she tried to refill my hot chocolate with coffee insisting that I had coffee. When the food arrived she got our orders mixed up. Which isn't a big deal at all and we weren't phased by it. 

Looking at the food everything looked great as always but because I ALWAYS order my eggs over easy I tend to jiggle my plate to do a quick check on my eggs and they seemed a little to wiggly. (I've been a server in a breakfast joint so I know how the eggs should be set when you move the plate) By this time our waitress had left the table. I cut into my eggs and they are literally not cooked. I get it, over easy is a runny egg which is never fully cooked but these eggs were completely uncooked. The egg whites looked like they do when you first crack an egg. I wait patiently for our waitress to return to request them recooked. When I explained the issue she looked at me and stated " Over easy eggs are always like that. " with quite a lot of attitude. I explained how they were supposed to be cooked and her response was " well that's how over easy eggs are cooked here, they're fine. " at this point I'm baffled by the fact she's arguing about this when you can clearly see clear gunk all over my plate. She takes my plate and with again a lot of attitude says she'll have them remade. She comes back and says she showed her manager and he said it's fine and they'll be remade. But you can tell she's not happy about it and that she didn't believe there was anything wrong. I get it she didn't cook the food but come on... you can't argue that the food was not cooked at all. The manager then brought my new plate to the table and our waitress barely came back to the table to check on us. She instantly gave us our check and didn't come back to refill any drinks. It sucks that this is the experience we had to deal with at one of our favorite restaurants. I'll go back because the food is amazing but I will NEVER allow her to be our server again. It was completely ridiculous and incredibly rude.

This place is one of my favorite coffee spots in Tampa. The inside is so bright and clean with tons of plants that make you feel at ease. The coffee is really good and they have milk alternatives. They almost went under because of COVID and they created new menu items for delivery to keep their business afloat. They also created and sold a really cute merch that was designed by a local artist and 100% of the proceeds went to their employees whose hours we're forced to be cut back. A business that cares about its employees speaks volumes and I'm glad to see a company I liked to step up in a time of need.
Food is great and smoothies are good.  Unfortunately the staff lacks personality and very uptight as well as the owners reflecting a snotty and pragmatic side to them.  No positive energy.

Dr Annabi has been my doctor for almost 8 years . Going back from the university days . He has always taken the time to help me and explain to me the differences between chronic pain and acute onset's how to manage it and how to block it . I have discovered different techniques with the help of Dr. Annabi to reduce my pain by 8 fold. His procedures have given 90 percent of my life back. . He has been a life saver for me . My debilitating disease took a toll on me for half my life . . I am able to enjoy my family time watching my grandchildren grow. I am able to provide and care for my family again. I have been able to live my life to the fullest with his amazing care . I am grateful for him and thank the lord everyday for bringing Dr. Annabi  into my life .after reading Joanne E review it's hard for me to believe that all these doctors are not helping her CRPS especially Dr Annabi. Seems to me Joanne is a real difficult person to deal with . I will send my blessings her way in order for her to find peace and serenity into her life as we all deserve a quality of life . If you are expecting a drug mill then you have the wrong place and wrong doctor . Their philosophy is to get to the root of the problem and try to solve where the pain is stemming from not to mask the pain . This makes me wonder if medications are all Joanne is looking for . I can almost bet it's all about the oxycodone for joanne . Which really just masks the pain . People are so caught up on these meds they forget the real REASON why DOCTORS are called DOCTORS and that is to figure out a way to cure someone's disease not mask it with narcotics that weren't made for chronic pain disorders . These people who love to destroy other people livelihoods are the ones who have destroyed what we call MEDICINE today. Spending tax payers dollars because of self righteous demands and wants . Psychologically and mentally ill behaviors who need to seek help ASAP for their mental illness not their CRPS. I could honestly say the Brain is a powerful tool and it can be used for so many positive ways but to use such malice and hate to represent a doctor visit that you had because your wants were not met is absolutely erroneous! I can only imagine how many other providers and lives you have sucked dry because of your self righteous . I sometimes am ashamed to live on this earth with people who are such self righteous people . Not a care in the world for the people who surround you. As a first world nation and leaders of the world in medicine why don't you focus your energy on finding a cure to you CRPS . Instead of focusing on writing such hate toward the ones who have literally given up half their live to take care of the human kind , who have helped thousands of sick patients through out their lives such as myself . Focus on positivity and discovering an ethical cure to your solutions . If rehab is one of those solutions then seek that too. If psychological is one of those solutions then seek that too. Try to focus your mind and attention on your disease instead of writing a one hour review In hopes to destroying a person.  I have dealt with many people such as yourself In the food industry and all I do is look and ask god to find a place to forgive this person . Those who move forward with a happy spirit will find that things always work out !

I just moved here from New Jersey. My mother had a massage at a moment peace many years ago and said we had to try it again. CHENOA did my manicure/pedicure. She was SOOO GOOD and kind and just a great person. I work in an operating room nearby and am on my feet constantly. She went well over and beyond the expected foot massage since she knew how much it meant to me. I scheduled another appointment to have her do it again in a month. Well worth the 30 minute drive from Nashville!!!

I'm going to be a little tough on this place because I expected absolute greatness, and I got something a little short of that.  

First, the food.  It is excellent, don't get me wrong.  I enjoy Mr Garces' work.  This was no different.  But, I was looking to be absolutely wowed by everything I ate.  I'd say I was mildly wowed by one thing I ate, and not as wowed by the other.  

The better choice was the short rib sandwich.  That was well constructed and very tasty.  It was also 10 bucks for a sandwich the size of my palm.  Now, I knew that going in.  I know the prices are what they are at a restaurant like this and I expect that.  I'm just saying that when you pay 10 bucks for a sandwich the size of your palm, it better be close to the best thing you ever ate in your life.  

The Albondigas were basically unusually flavored meatballs surrounding a poached egg in a special sauce with a couple of pieces of bread.  While I enjoyed their flavor, it wasn't special to me.  For 10 bucks, I want to get wowed.  I don't want to think that I've had meatballs just as good at a Delco firehouse wedding. 

So that's the food, and I'm basing the three star review on that alone.  The following is just the rantings of a guy from Delco trying to figure out this whole Philly trendy dining scene.  

Being one person trying to dine here without a reservation on a Saturday night, I realize that is a challenge.  I asked about tables and was told there wouldn't be one until 9.  I get that.  I'm asking a lot by showing up without notice, and there isn't much space at the crowded bar.  

Of course, the reason there wasn't much space is that two girls decided to save a third seat for their friend who was showing up later (to the point that when I asked if the end seat was open, they said it wasn't, moved to that seat, and put all of their stuff on the middle seat between them... and that person didn't show up for the entire time I was there), and a party of three who sat down at the bar before me decided to stay at the bar even after being offered a table in the dining room.  This while knowing there were people wanting to sit at the bar all along.  Their apologies to me were hollow.  If you get a table, take the table and let some standing people at the bar have a shot.  Just my opinion, and a reason why I don't frequent Center City trendy spots nearly as much.  I could be wrong but I consider these things ignorance.  

So I got to stand up in the back of the bar and eat off a counter like I was at Pat's Steaks.  While I accept it as a natural part of the layout of this place, let's just say it didn't add to my experience one bit.  I know some of these Garces locations have little space.  It's part of the deal (I'm a veteran of Village Whiskey next door and I have been turned away more than once).  I'm just saying that part of the experience isn't exactly a plus.  

Again, if you're going to cramp the layout of an area of the restaurant like that, you'd better have the best food I ever had for those prices.  It didn't happen.

It was a disappointment staying at this hotel. While the room is spacious, the finishes and amenities are out of date. Hotel air circulation is poor. Walls are thin where you can clearly hear your arguing neighbors next door. Service is ok, but valet parking guys are polite and helpful. For the high price paid, being outdated and so so customer service, I would chose other options for my next stay.

The absolute best place on earth to buy glasses and sunglasses! The customer service is exceptional and the selection is amazing. They are always getting new things in, making the hardest thing about the visit choosing which frames you're going to get! I have a few pairs of glasses from here and they are great at readjusting them any time I need. I really feel valued as a customer. 
There products are very high quality and extremely original!

Absolutely great! Our waitress Danielle did not disappoint.  She was welcome and just had a positive vibe that made it easy to ask questions and listen to her suggestions.  We were celebrating two birthdays and she acknowledged both birthday guests at our table. Something small but it really makes a difference in your experience. Food was great no complaints about anything. Cooked to temperatures asked with decent portions. My only complaint was that we made reservations and was first given a booth that would experience too much foot traffic from other guests.  We asked to be moved and we were moved. I was a little annoyed that we were even given that booth.  Seats near restrooms or entrance should be for those who show up demanding tables and wanting immediate service without reservations.

Strange experience! I went for an alcoholic slushy, got the Secret Lovers. The slushy itself was yummy. However, I guess for COVID you have to mix your own drink. They give you a bag with airplane bottles along with your slushy. It was a little awkward to do while walking around Soulard.

Instead of the advertised liquors, (I think it was supposed to be schnapps and peach Pearl Vodka) I was given 2 airplane bottles of 99 Peaches. It was still good but I was disappointed that wasn't reflected on the menu. The price was also $2 higher than indicated on the menu. 

I will say they did a good decent job with covid precautions, everyone had masks and only two people at a time were allowed inside. I'd give them another try post-covid times.

Love New Hope, but can't say the same about this place.

I actually think my meal there was the worst edible food I've ever been presented in a restaurant.  It's not that it was vile, stale, or of some other unappetizing quality, but rather, it was some of the most tasteless, bland, and overall unenjoyable food I've ever been served.

Ordered some sort of quesadilla that consisted of chicken and a variety of undercooked vegetables that would be better suited for a chicken pot pie.  Everything was thrown under a flour tortilla blanket, which makes me question the bold liberty which was taken when writing the menu and calling this dish a quesadilla.  Also, the store-bought salsa and small bunch of generic nacho chips on the side didn't do any favors.

I'd love to go into the bare specifics of what made it so awfully tasteless, but I feel as though it's not even worth any sort of description.  My two fellow diners had better experiences, but were both highly underwhelmed with their respective Thai dishes.

All in all, only went because it looked pleasant from the outside.  Definite charm and a welcoming atmosphere, yet it all falls apart once the food comes to the table.

Just tried today while exploring Boise with my kiddos.  Staff was super friendly and helpful.  They seat you if you are dine in to keep social distance.  The food was Delicious!!! We tried the Turkey, Salami, Sausage and Fluffernutter sandwiches as well as the tomato soup.  Everything was yummy and flavorful.  The contrast of flavors in each sandwich was awesome.  The bread appeared to be super fresh and crusty.  Would recommend in a heartbeat.  Also the prices were reasonable for portions.  Will be back if we come back to Boise.

Best wedding cakes in Tucson.  They did an outstanding job for our wedding.  We were highly satisfied.  Also, the princess cakes are the best cakes that you can order anywhere.  They will even custom design them to some extent.  Great job!
Customer service was great, they take their jobs very seriously. The yogurt was great and the fruit was so fresh!

Watched the movie hunger games part 3

Good seating, good sound system. Get the bucket of popcorn it saves you money when you go back to the movies. Free refills too

Ordered online and food was ready on time.  Love the various sauces - got whole chicken with yucca fries, chicken soup, and and plantains.  All three sides were delicious.  Chicken was juicy and flavorful.  Fed our family of four for $25.  My kids actually ate their food!  Eat here...I'm thinking about picking up from here everyday...

This was my debut visit with my gf and we picked it from a random Yelp search for ethnic-based brunch spots. I am a pancake or steak eggs and taters kinda brunch person as anyone knows so a stretch to try Mexican was certainly a push for me. 

We got in right at 11am when they open and got seated quick. The menu is slim but looks appealing and unique. I was really hungry as I am most Sunday's for brunch. I went with the seafood Colcetel. My GF went with chilaquiles. We were both a little surprised at the appetizer size portions of our meals (we were thinking typical big plate brunch so our bad) my cocktail was as the picture shows a (delicious) but very small wine glass sized cocktail of fish and shrimp in a nice sweet and spicy sauce I did like. 5 minutes later I was done and still hungry. 

My GF bowl was basically some queso, 1 fried egg, a good sauce and allot of tortilla. No beans or meat which I had always thought was standard for chilaquiles. 

My dish was $16 and hers was $12. I feel like we could have gotten allot more filling meal of traditional brunch fare at our usual spots which I prefer for a brunch when I skip normal 8am breakfast. The food is good, service is great and the venue looks cool. We peaked at a dinner menu and found many plates we really want to try as we both love pulpo and short rib and mole' sauces. Perhaps that would be a more wise pick vice for brunch.

I would and will be back for dinner but not likely for brunch.

I can hardly lift my fingers to write this review due to my state of utter food-coma.

I needed a quick lunch in Center City and as usual Yelp delivered. While I wanted to spend veritable hours wandering in Reading Terminal Market, I politely battled my way to the back wall occupied by Meltkraft and settled in to wait. The line was short - only 3 people ahead of me - and I needed every second of that time to angst about which of their entertainingly-named chalkboard offerings I would spend my hard-earned money on.

I finally settled on the Brielle, as I was feeling sweet at that moment, with a side of tomato soup, although I was sorely tempted by the Melter Skelter and its promise of pickled green tomatoes. My sandwich took 4-5 minutes to make, which I spent chatting amicably with the staff and getting recommendations for the best mocha nearby. And then... oh god. From the first bite of this perfect creation, I knew that there was nothing more that I wanted to eat for the rest of my life. The creamy texture of the melted brie was just where I wanted it, with the slight crunch of its caramelized onions and the delicious sweetness of the accompanying raisins providing the perfect accompaniment. It only got better when dipped in the roasted tomato soup, which created a fantastic savory contrast. 

Chips? Eh. Crumble some up and put them in the soup, or just ignore them. Whatever. Follow it up with a black & white from 4th Street Bakery and you'll be much happier.

I don't know if I'm just not used to eating greasy/cheesy/bready things, but this meal filled me up like nobody's business. Meltkraft, I'm coming back for you.... in a year, when I feel hungry again.

It's good for what it is. It's a local club with most of the essentials. It's not big and new, but it's definitely doable for a good work out. It's not crowded and there's always parking.

There's a lot of good helpful people who work there like Jeff, Sierra, Kelcie, Lauren, and Kelly.

My husband and I were there July 23rd for early anniversary gift we totally enjoyed ourselves. The food was amazing the audience was great and the staff was great. 
We can't wait to go back.

Been here plenty of times before but this write up is for my latest outing there, Sunday Brunch.  These days were looking for places that accomadate strollers, other than maybe Kildares, on main street.  Although there was a function going on we were able to get a table for 6 for brunch outside.  

It was excellent.  Great service.  Very friendly.  Half off bloody marys and mamosas.  The only option is the break/lunch buffet for $21.95, I think.  It was awesome.  Turkey and beef carving stations, omlette bar,  fresh lox, the breakfast essentials, some hot lunch items too.  Really great.  Good to check out.
Overpriced touristy seafood trap.  Slow service.  Food was mediocre and doesn't match up to plenty of other options in the city.

Surf & Turf Enchiladas. So satisfying with every bite. Salmon so deliciously grilled by fire. 
We had to eat half our portions to save room for dessert. Tres Leches topped off a scrumptious meal. Got to take home half our meal & enjoy the next day!

Sperry's is a Nashville original restaurant, I was around when the first one opened in Belle Meade-we have eaten there many times, now we are more likely to eat in Cool Springs.  The steaks are very good, I particularly like "oscar style" with crabmeat and asparagus on top-what a treat.  They have delicious wines and the salad bar is a must-but be careful with the salad and bread, you may fill up before your dinner arrives!

This place doesn't even deserve one star! If there was an award for the most unconcerned, shrew of a veterinarian in Pinellas County, it goes to this incompetent 'doctor' who runs a shit show. My friend took her precious animal there. Dr. Matt is neglectful, and his malpractice is going to get him in big trouble! He didn't even look at the animal for more than 5 seconds before prescribing pill after pill to get her money. I ADVISE EVERYONE, if you care about your pet at all, do NOT bring them to this place.

American Sleep Medicine did not provide all the facts concerning insurance. They "forgot" to mention that they were outside of my network. Sooooo....instead of paying 20% I am being charged 8000. Aside from that my before and after visit with the physician was less than 5 minutes. GO some place else. It seems they are concerned only with the dollars they make and not the patient.

Fun restaurant right on Beach Dr.  Outside seating.  Happy hour specials.  Decent beer on tap selection.  The colonialism vibe is not weird at all...........

I ate here twice during my stay.  First was for lunch with half order of fish and chips, which was still pretty big. I also had the crab curry soup.  Fish and chips were great.  Soup was good.  

Second was for dinner.  I had Shepard's pie and it was very good.  Table had two full orders of fish and chips....looked like a whole filet as the order was huge.  Also a puff pasty and curry dish.  Everyone enjoyed their meals.  The curry was just okay.  

Pierogie appetizer was a hit with butter and onions and even some pieces of sausage.

Service was nice but seemed a bit busy during dinner.

My husband and I continue to be impressed with the staff and the work of North Penn Art. We have had numerous pieces of art and sports jerseys framed at North Penn Art and they are all done well, with a quick turn around and impeccable service! Thank goodness for their artistic ideas because our projects always come out better than we envision:) We highly recommend!

This is hands down my go to breakfast spot in town. The service is ALWAYS exceptional and they really go above and beyond to make a great experience. Also, v good looking staff, esp the tall one on register.  Coffee is solid, food is always delish. 10/10 would recommend.

Their Gelato is SO wonderful. 


They're always changing out flavors, the workers are very nice and never reluctant to let you try too many flavors (don't be a prick and take advantage though)

Some of their flavors are even stated in italiano, (Che divertente!) And while the pricing gets steeper with the size of Gelato increasing, the taste is great quality and rich.  

I love spoon!

This little store is a friend to row-home folk. It has all the things you need to do those pesky little chores around the house. 
I usually let all the little jobs pile up until I have the gumption to drive to South Philly to one of the major hardware chains. Once in these behemoth stores I am instantly overwhelmed by all the product that is for major home renovation. 
At Rittenhouse Hardware, you will easily find everything you need for the fix this and touch up that situations that seem to arise more often than you would like. A small space with a ton of stuff, it is pretty easy for even a novice to find what you need. Helpful young staff will give you advice if you need it. 
While browsing the shelves I found more than I needed, so be careful. You may go in for a nut and bolt,  and come back with the makings for a whole new project.

Etch was memorable.  The name fits.
We arrived early, a good habit that I am picking up (I'm not living up to my name)
and the hostess sat us immediately.  I was not too pleased with the table, it was next to the window, but it was only two of us, so I really couldn't complain.  The decor was simple yet chic.  Very zen. 

Our waiter showed up immediately and introduced himself, and gave us time to look through the wine list.  We never felt rushed or forgotten.  We settled on a simple Spanish Syrah ( their wine prices are reasonable). 

After the presentation of the wine, the waiter went through the menu with us and answered all of our questions.  To me that is a plus when the wait staff knows the menu.

The two appetizers were outstanding!
The roasted cauliflower drizzled with truffle
oil was amazing and it came with with crema that was blended with feta cheese that was indescribable.  The pork belly was seasoned and cooked to perfection.

The Etch salad was good, but I could have gone for more cauliflower.  

Now the entree, I had the fillet, med. rare, sitting on top of puree of potatoes, and dressed with peeled asparagus.  The fillet was so good, ate all of my steak and left the sides there.  Needed room for dessert.

After much thought, we finally narrowed it down to the rhubarb and pecan tart.  One word - delicious. 

Great food, great service and great ambience.

this place is horrible they dont care if your car is clean or not as long as you paid. It would be a better carwash if they actually had workers that know what they are doing including management talking to josh is like talking to dog they hear you but will they choose to listen,  they hire a bunch of school kids at minimum wage beside getting some people in there that actually wanna work and detail cars the right way but no one is gonna give a full 110% at 8.25 an hour. moral of it all is the owners are stingy as shitt and they wanna get every car out of there as fast as possible rather its clean or not better luck to yall hope u take this into consideration GET SOME ACTUAL DETAILERS AND MANAGERS you would make twice the money since thats all you guys care about......
I had the caramel ice cream and it was intense and amazing! I also was tempted by the Thai peanut option - loved the cayenne pepper kick it offers. I bought the salted caramel sauce it was so delish.

Excellent thin crust pizza.  I am from New England not far from New Haven, CT and this is the closest I have found to Pepe's Pizza (Pepe's where every president and pope has been since it opened in the 1920s... Obama hasn't been there YET...) My favorite is the white clam with mushrooms... I just wish they were open more often for lunch.

Ate here once two months ago.  The shrimp appetizer was very interesting - definitely recommend it.

The place was laid back and the food enjoyable, worth trying it. If it's closed, walk up the street and get a turkey sandwich at Grumpy's.

It's my boyfriend and I's go to spot before movie dates.  Its quiet and cute. Simple decore, and everyone who has helped us has been friendly.  I am a fan of the Veggie sandwich, but all of the special of the week sandwiches I have tried have been tasty as well. The tomato soup is my go to on a cold day.

I had a hard time finding it because google map said that it was on the other corner of the building. literally had to park the car (which park isnt easy in downtown Tampa) and walked around to find it. The coffee was good but in my opinion i prefer Buddy Brew. It looks clean and the server is friendly. Good environment to chill.
Perfect steaks, delicious homemade sauces, awesome deserts! The atmosphere is relaxed but classy, friendly waiters and the price acceptable for the great quality! Highly recommended!

So so so overpriced. $10 for a SMALL bowl!! So crazy to me. For some reason I still find myself coming back. The mixture in the pitaya bowl is great and they give you enough toppings to pitaya mixture ratio. However for $10 I could make one at home by myself!!

Service, ordering options, and the size of this place give it 4 stars.  I had my first hot chicken the night before in East Nashville and I loved it.  But this place left some to be desired.  I ordered "jumbo" wings and 2 sides for $10.  These wings were the same size as the place that night before which doesn't try to make them sound bigger.  They use a dry rub on the wings.  I went with medium and it was pretty well flavored.  I think I should have tried hot to push my limits as this was an easy medium spice. 

The sides were a big let down here.  I ordered Mac N Cheese and compared to the place the night before  blewh.  I gave it to my wife who liked it better than the night before.  The fried Okra was pretty good, doesn't have much flavor but I could eat that over beans or potato salad.  The beans were your basic canned beans and the potato alas could have been made at any grocer.  

My wife ordered the paperback cheese and tenders.  They deep dry a pepper jack grilled cheese and then place tenders on top.  She order it lightly mild and it was mild.  The tenders were decent size and good quality meat.  The deep fried cheese sandwich tasted like a large cheese stick.  I wish they would have added cheese with more of a kick.  I wouldn't order this as it was lackluster to me.  

Service is great here as they take your phone number and text you when your food is done.  We were able to run over to Auto Zone. And. Uh a few groceries as we waited.  The inside is very nice decent sized groups could enjoy this place.  The lady at the window was very helpful and super nice.  She helped keep this review a 4 star because the food left me wishing for the night before.

An awesome shop! I play other instruments and have been hearing accordion for a minute in my  
I took a 1/2 hr lesson on the basics and then played some accordions to see which one felt the best .

They answered all my questions and really took the time to help me get familiar 

They also have a great trade up program that let's you keep improving your choice of accordion as you improve 

I highly recommend this shop for anyone checking out an accordion

Overall just not impressive in terms of coffee or crepes. I ordered the nutty, which was coffee flavored with almond. I love almond and had high hopes for the drink, but the flavor combination seemed a little off. I prefer the more savory crepes so I went with a mushroom spinach crepe. The crepe mostly consisted of scrambled eggs leaving the flavor fairly bland. Not a bad experience but not impressive enough that I would likely return.

Much better than expected, pleasantly surprised, kinda blown away actually. (It's a fast-food pizza/salad joint, I was honestly expecting Little Caesar's or Domino's quality). Nope. We ordered a pizza and a salad and both were excellent. The price is right too. Workers are friendly and helpful. Place is clean and has a nice setup. Decent selection of beverages, including beer. Watch this franchise expand all over the place. Great concept with a solid execution. 5 stars all around.

One of our go-to taco place in town! Went there for the Fourth of July collab with Hi-Point--cheeseburger taco! Was fantastic and really hope that could become a regular on the menu! But actually all of their tacos are great! And cannot leave without finishing with some crispy churros and warm chocolate sauce!

Their food is not the best Mexican food; however, it is pretty good. I like the fact that they are authentic and not Americanized. Every time I call in the place an order, the girl is extremely polite. I also like the fact that they deliver in a timely fashion. When my arrive arrives, it is always warm. Give this place a try if you're in the mood for authentic Mexican food.

Not only is the food great but the presentation is so pretty that you almost don't want to disturb your plate!  

The food is quite lovely and you never know what you will be eating since the menu changes daily.  

If you are vegan, this is not the place for you!  There is one vegetarian dish offered each day but you can count on meat heavy offerings.  

The day we went, we had the vegetarian tamales and they were delicious!
Very good stuff, super friendly staff, but too much buttercream frosting. Made my teeth hurt!

Quick, easy, and tasty!

You sit down at the bar, a waiter comes right up to you and takes your order, and prepares is fresh on the grill.

I had the Manhattan omelet, and it was huge! Your menu serves as your receipt and you're on your way. Definitely a good place to grab a quick breakfast on the go.
Horrible, filthy, low quality food. We had the worst experience and people were very rude. The worst was the cashier. She should work in a correctionsl facility. What a horrible experience!

I ordered a new iPhone through the store. I worked with Sam and he was very helpful!  Once I received the phone at home, I took it back to the store and worked with Sam again to get it set up, activated and syncing with my Apple Watch. I was extremely pleased with the service!  I would  recommend working with Sam!
Terrible management. People are rude and disorganized. Will never recommend to anyone especially walks in. They take whoever they want and use appointments as an excuse.  Walk ins are not welcome.

We have a long relationship with Dr. Katie and our labs.  She is awesome, as is the rest of the staff there.  They are knowledgeable and empathetic -- both are necessary for our furry family.
It is a nice modern facility with plenty of room for the pets.
Good service, good food, great cocktails. I had the Korean beef tacos and a margarita and it was excellent. The atmosphere is great and prices reasonable

On a whim we stopped in for lunch. The decor is typical of a Chinese restaurant in a small strip mall. Small quiet and comfortable. My wife ordered the sesame chicken and I  ordered the Mongolian beef. The kitchens timing was off and my wife's did came out way before mine did. She was halfway done her entree before mine came out. I tried a bit of her.entree and it was very good. Lightly breaded chicken and a sauce that did not hide the taste of the chicken. Very nice. When my entree arrived I was pleasantly surprised. Tender beef, onions and bell peppers in a pepper sauce that was worth the wait. A nice dose of heat and yet I could still taste the sweetness of the onions. A dish that was well done by the chef. We will return!

Waked in... been months since I was here...
Waiting.... WAITING WAITING 4 people in restaurant and yet... TO BUSY TO SIT ME DOWN...

Horrible customer service....
The customer service at this bank is amazing! They really care for their clients. And the cookies and coffee are a yummy bonus. ;)

The best Greek food in town! 
Always good service and good food. 
A must try if you're in the Reno/Sparks area. 
My favorite thing to eat is there is a gyro with fries! Everything is made to order & fresh.
Julie my server told me my food looked gross. Give the sushi chef a raise and fire your waitresses.

Nathaniel is the man, very honest and reliable, saved me over 10k today as someone tried to convince me that my ac unit was dead and needed to be replaced. Nathaniel came  out and had it working within 30 minutes, I definitely recommend his company for any hvac needs. I just read the reviews for Flash heating and home repair company and I am upset that people would leave a negative review given that this had to do with scheduling an appointment and not actually servicing the hvac system. It's like me leaving a restaurant 1 star review without trying their food all because I couldn't be accommodated with my reservations, pure nonsense. Flash heating and Home Repair gets 5 stars from me for work excellently done.

This is now one of my top taco places to hit up in Indy.  There are a lot to choose from but I loved the vibe of Cholita's as well as there options.  All the tacos we had where topped with unique ingredients to give each taco an individual taste!  Not to mention the salsa which had a nice, roasted flavor that really added depth more than your typical run of the mill salsa.  The food came in a very timely manner and our waiter was always checking in!  We will be going back soon for sure!

4 stars because my mother and friend had to wait an extremely long time to receive services. We went in on a Thursday morning. We had an appointment slot for our wedding group and they promised that we could all be together. I understand that we had 7 people, but I wish they would have told me they were working on getting my mom/friend a service technician instead of letting them sit unattended. We had to get up a few times and go talk to the front desk to get someone working with my mom/friend. 

That being said, my nails and toes looked great for the big day. I enjoyed the top-level pedicure and he was very gentle with my feet. I got dip on my hands and I wasn't happy with the color (you could still see the white of my nails underneath) so the awesome nail guy patiently redid the top two layers so my nails were good to go for wedding photos. I appreciate all of their hard work. My girls all loved their nails. Would definitely return.
Also, SO MANY BUGS - spiders. I've complained twice to the office about them multiple times with no acknowledgement. They are bringing in an exterminator, finally.

If I could give 0 stars, I would.  I went to Duafe after hearing rave reviews from a friend who is loc'd.  At the time, I was a novice to natural hair care, but knew that i did not want locs or coils.  I made an appointment for a consultation and arrived on time.  When I walked in, I was not greeted and kind of stood in the middle of the shop looking to see if anyone would actually come say anything to me.  

Gerber (i only remember the name because it is uncommon) came and handed me a form to fill out and then came back to give me a book of pictures.  My hair at the time was short, as I was in the process of growing it out from a short cut.  There was no relaxer in my hair, and I was wearing it as a wash n go (learned the term later), so my hair appeared extra curly and fine.  It was actually loaded with gel giving it that appearance.  Gerber never touched my hair and she sat across from me in a chair the whole time (some consultation).  She didn't even look like she was interested, and acted as if she was sleepy or too tired to talk to me.  If about 10 minutes of pretty much silence (as I looked through the picture book) she told me that locs or coils were my only option.

I said "thanks" and walked out.  I never scheduled an appointment with them, and I'm glad I didn't.  I found sites like curlynikki.com and YT videos and I now care for and do my hair myself!  I guess you have to be Jill Scott to receive stellar service in Duafe.

This was our third stop going around wine tasting over the weekend and we were all very impressed with their wine selection and overall taste. They have a great deal that if you purchase the glass for $5, you get the glass itself and 5 tastings that day. Whenever you bring the glass back you get unlimited tastings! The two people who helped us out were really informative and nice as well. 

The reason I didn't give a full 5 stars is because they are currently under construction (which isn't what bothered me), but what it actually looked like before these renovations. It was in serious need of updating because the space & wine itself is great. I'm excited to see what it looks like after all the additions are done! Which apparently should be sometime in April.

Had a blast at Yazoo Brewery. The brewery tour was the perfect blend of tasting, learning about the company history and the brew process itself. Our guide, Lucas, balanced his knowledge of the product with a great sense of humor, creating an enjoyable experience for all. We went to the taproom on a Saturday and it was definitely a great atmosphere. Both bachelor and bachelorette parties were welcomed as well as couples and groups of friends. All I wish is that the great beers of Yazoo were available in Chicago.

Brought a visitor from out of town. Had heard rave reviews of the place. It was awful. The oysters had too much breading on them . The barbecue shrimp po boy was not spicy at all and had baby shrimp on it. Something like 70 count. Will never eat there again. What a poor example of what a New Orleans po boy should be.
First timer and will definitely be back to try more! Had the spicy chicken wrap. Not too spicy just the right kick. Kale salad on the side was a nice addition.

The worst ever. Complained about dirty coffee cup and asked for a clean one. I made sure to notice where the cracks on it were. Lo and behold! The "clean" cup brought back had the exact cracks and now a "swipe" mark most likely from a dirty rag. The carpet and table were dirty too by the way. The eggs were cooked perfectly. Over easy. Pretty much the only thing edible. The hash browns were so crispy that the steak knife for the chicken fried CRAP wouldn't even cut them. Then there was the chicken fried CRAP. Where is the "steak" in this? Or is it just deep fried, tasteless breading with a GLOP of even less tasty flour mixed with water atop it?! Needless to say, I won't be back to this hole.
