Eating now and don't want to stop to write this review, amazing is all I need to say. We ordered the flank skewers, the Kobe sliders, bacon wrapped dates, and the prime filet medallions. All were amazing

Wonderful little authentic Mexican restaurant in cozy Lambertville, right across the river from New Hope. Even though they misplaced our reservation for 10 people we had only to wait 10 minutes on a Saturday night to be seated. 

The restaurant itself is quaint and decorated with quite a few pictures of buhos, or owls. Service was fantastic, the wait staff was incredibly friendly. My favorite part of the whole evening was the free chips and salsa they start you off with when you sit down. Not only were the chips delicious and fresh, but they came with 3 different types of salsas that were all amazing. 

Our food was prepared well and from what I tasted around the table, everything was excellent, no complaints from anyone in our party of 10. As it was a birthday dinner, they came out with a piece of cake for the guest of honor and had one of the chefs serenade her with a really nice song in Spanish which actually brought my mother to tears (which could have been a result of the BYOB wine but it was nice singing regardless). I'm not sure what type of cake it was but for someone who normally doesn't like cake this dessert was absolutely delightful. 

I definitely recommend Buho, outstanding service, delicious authentic Mexican cuisine, and very reasonable prices.

This place is the most amazing joint for hand crafted cocktails in Tucson. We enjoyed everything on the menu. Erick was an amazing bartender and make us complex, smooth, delicious drinks. Come here for the best cocktails you've ever had.

Here's what I loved: surprising flavors I adored.
Here's what I hated: can't think of anything.

We stopped in here because it was 90 degrees out and needed somewhere to sit and have a cold beer. IT was the only place without a line. 

We ordered our beers, waited for about 15 minutes for our order to be taken,. then waited about an hour for the food. Not only did it take forever to get the food, but my steak and cheese was cold by the time I got it!

Golden Coast is by far my favorite Chinese restaurant in Nashville. The food is great all the time, but you absolutely must try the Sunday buffet. On Sunday they switch to their "authentic" menu and the proportion of Chinese clientele greatly increases which is always a good sign. They have those squishy bean and rice deserts and soy milk on the buffet along with bubble tea and veggie egg rolls - all of which are disappointingly absent on all the other buffets I try (or even on the main menu at some places).  

The owners are amazing. When I lived in that part of town I went all the time, and to this day the owner still remembers and teases me about my obsession with bubble tea. He has even sneaked the occasional to go cup of it to me (though I promised I wouldn't tell so, shhhh). They are also willing to add to the buffet if for some reason the veggie options aren't there as usual.

I am definitely enamored with this place. I don't make it to that part of town as much these days though, so if you go pick up some tofu and vegetables for me.

I love PF! The gym is nice and clean- very much equipment to target any area of your body for full workouts. There is no way you cannot give PF a 5 star... You can't beat 10 bucks a month with a bat! Awesome place!

I was referred to them by Marlton Lock and Safe. My car key broke out of the key fob. I called JR Flood for information and price. They suggested a refurbished one for way less than a new fob. The dealership was over $270.00, another locksmith was $145.00 new. I went right down and they fixed it in about 20 minutes! 
I highly recommend this amazing place in the mart. Very nice and great prices. Very knowledgeable also. Great team there that works hard and does honest work fast! I will refer and return for more key issues!
Great doctors office if you're a drug addict looking for pills,  terrible place for people looking for medical assitance. Rude staff and under educated physicians.
This is my first time here and I'm in love with their food! I got the firecracker Burger and boys my face wedding! This is my new regular place for burgers , I give it a high five!

This will be my first review, as I plan to try it again.  I don't know how my opinion could be so off from everyone elses.'

First off, the prices at this place cannot be beat! 

Food - I will need to order something different next time.  I got the chicken in clay pot, chicken soup and the vegan summer roll.  The vegan summer role was not very good.  I have had summer rolls at other places that are far better and the dipping sauce far more authentic.  The chicken soup was lack luster and had thick rice noodles in it.  The noodles were not cooked very well and basically took over the entire dish.

My main dish was alright.  It was just chicken with green beans.  It was cooked well but just seemed off with the jasmine rice.  Maybe the chicken should be eaten by itself or with some sort of sauce.  It was not very good in my opinion.

Restaurant interior is basic.  Just tables upon tables and simple table clothes.  

I will review this place again as I typically agree with fellow yelpers and am surprised that my experience was so off.

Update (albeit a little late!):   Bert came out and fixed our hot tub in just one visit, and for MUCH less money and time than I had expected. He was prompt and as always, professional. I ordered a new filter and chemicals from Sam over the phone and they had them in quickly. I was able to drive over to their home in Exton / West Chester area to pick things up. This saved me the cost of shipping and I was able to get them faster too. Again... GREAT service! I highly recommend BP Spa Repair for anyone looking for excellent service at a fair price. Thanks Bert and Sam!

Just two employees present, one doesn't do anything except gossip. They were running an hour behind, even for appointments. Terrible place... save yourself the pain and go to Craycroft location. 20 people in Wilmot waiting area and 1 in Craycroft.

I have never stepped foot in the actual bar, but I have gotten food delivered at least 10 times at this point. There are many options for tacos in the city but I keep coming back here. I have had the Shrimp Tacos, the Korean Tacos, Chicken Quesadilla, Fries, Plantains, Chips and Guac, and Churros. 

Appetizers: Chips and guac are always fresh and delicious, a little on the pricey side compared to other places around the city, but they give a good portion and it's tasty so it's not a problem

The fries here are plentiful and the Mayo dipping sauce is a perfect touch. I love french fries, but would rarely get them at a taco spot. This place is the exception.

Entrees: Korean Tacos are FANTASTIC! I want to try something new every time, but I just can't get myself to do it. The short ribs are tender, there is a nice kick, the kimchi isn't overpowering and the chipotle mayo brings a coolness to the dish. I strayed once and got the Shrimp Taco and it was a mistake, it just couldn't compete.

My wife gets the chicken quesadilla, she's pretty particular about her quesadillas and she keeps going back

Dessert: Churros and Plantains. The churros are crispy and the two sauces (chocolate and dulce de leche) were outstanding, I want to dip everything in it. Those plantains are some of the best I've had. They come with a honey and peanut crumble, the stickiness, crunch, and soft plantain come together nicely and it's a hefty portion.

Chips and Guac 4/5
Korean Tacos 5/5
Shrimp Tacos 4/5
Chicken Quesadilla 5/5
French Fries 5/5
Churros 4/5
Plantains 5/5

Came here for a date night on a Saturday. Wasn't too busy being a weekend. I really am glad they gave Valet parking, the gentleman are really nice, and it's only 15$ and I drop my car right at the front of the resturaunt and pick it up right there too. Saves time and money and they are really quick and reliable. 
Overall dining experience was great. The hostess was nice, we sat for about 5 mins before being sat. We came about 15 mins earlier than the reservation.  
Our waiter was very very accommodating. He acknowledged my Yelp offer for 1 free artisan dipper when you check into the location. Even though he has never seen it he made sure he talked to the manager and they took it off on the bill. So that was really great! He was polite and quick given he had A LOT of tables to take care of. He explained everything for us to make sure we got the best dining experience. We did the Alpine cheese dip (my favorite), 2 Caesar salads, 1 classic entree, and the s'mores dessert fondue. The bill came out to be 51$ !!! Talk about saving money, usually for two people it's 100$++ ... but I have been here before and know how much food it could be and I got smart when ordering. We decided to share an entree because the cheese fondue plus the salad is already filling before the dinner comes out. And we had plenty room for the dessert. 

I believe our waiters name was Silver? He was absolutely great! We had such a great experience. 

Also, a tip is to try not to order any drinks, it helps with the bill later on. Granted there cocktails are amazing! But if you wanna save money either drink before or after. Going there for the fondue experience is the best.

Walk by this place and decided to stop in for breakfast.  It did not disappoint!!  The biscuits are awesome and lots of different choices.  The Southern Chicken Biscuit was out of this world!  I could have eaten two of them!!  A must when in Nashville

I can't believe I haven't been here before!
My daughter brought me here last night to try the ceviche and the ahi tuna tacos because I told her I was trying to keep it light and healthy-  I had no idea they have a "fit" menu with several optionS. (Not so common at Mexican restaurants!)
I almost slipped, tempted by the sound of crawfish enchilada, lol, but I LOVED the ceviche and ahi tacos!!
They also serve a very large basket of thin, crispy chips and great salsa but I didn't feel like I needed them at all. 
We also ordered margaritas, a frozen and a rocks, and I thought they were very good
Most importantly, our waiter was amazing.  I always go back for the service!

Foods really good not for a bad price either. Really authentic Mexican food in northwest tucson. Great Mexican environment that reminds me of my nanas kitchen. Strongly recommend coming here if you want a taste for Mexican.

Completely ripped off for an oil change! $66.00 never coming back! Staying with my dealership. He also was trying to convince me not to go back to the Pep Boys that was close to my house oh don't worry about it I will be going to any pep boys anymore!
not the same anymore. new owner? new name? new menu. disappointing lol. bring back perkins and the good food /:

Been here three times and my stomach has never felt worse. Don't buy their lattes! 

The food is fine here and tastes like every other place.

Gus's is in my opinion a french loaf cooked to a pretzel. I swear I have seen french loafs the same size. My wife and I stop at Gus's when we are on the way to Chicago. She would rate them a 5 for sure. I just am not crazy about a big hunk of dough with a golden crust. When I order I make sure a get the cheese dip so I can mask some of the bread with cheese. I have eaten the pretzel brat once. It was a 4 Tums brat. Way too much grease embedded into the dough. I know I know I am from St. Louis and should be loyal and vote 5 stars but I just can't. If you are from St. Louis or from other parts Gus is unique nuff said.

We enjoyed a satisfying vegetarian dinner here. It was refreshing to have a vegetarian place we could get excited about in Nashville. There was a 30 minute wait. It's a small space (I would guess they can seat 30 people if every chair is taken) and pretty loud inside. I had the black bean burger which comes with a side.  The burger well seasoned and reasonably moist, my side of chick pea salad was seasoned with fresh herbs and resembled the texture of chicken salad. My dining companion enjoyed the portabella quinoa bowl which had lots of olive and sundried tomato flavor. The prices are reasonable and our waiter was attentive. The bathroom was very unpleasant and parking was very difficult (we walked about 4 blocks and that was as close as we could get with a legal parking space).

Stayed here overnight this past weekend. Everything was clean and in good order for our stay. Staff was nice and helpful. Close walking distance to the stadium. I would stay here again in a heartbeat.
We eat here all the time!  Still one of the best Italian restaurants in Cwood.  The service is great, and they always remember who we are.

My first appointment was a routine visit. The doctor briefly looked into my ear, and decided that I needed a CAT scan, and then told me to make a follow-up appointment in 4 to 6 weeks. The following week, I had the CT scan done, and then I made my appointment for 4 weeks after my initial visit. 
Two days before the second appointment, I received a bill in the mail that was higher than what my insurance company Explanation of Benefits (EOB) said I had to pay. I called the billing person, and right off the bat, she was very rude, stating that I needed to pay what they charged. If I didn't know any better, the way she handled this made me think this is a common event. I decided that I would bring the bill in, so that I could discuss this fault in person, perhaps with someone with more poise and consideration.
On the day of my scheduled appointment, I showed up on time. The front desk person said that in order to be seen, I needed to pay today's co-payment, plus the remaining balance. I stated I would pay today's co-payment, but that I would like to resolve the error in the unpaid balance. She stated that I would need to speak with the Office Manager, and resolve any billing issues prior to being seen. I told her that I had just received the bill only two days before. She said that it didn't matter, and that payment was expected now.
I waited 20 minutes in the waiting room for the Office Manager. He led me to an office, and stated that I needed to pay the bill undisputedly. I showed him the Explanation of Benefits from the insurance company, showing I owed less than this bill. After asking me if I was really going to dispute 15$, he agreed that I owed less, and it needed to be paid now. He was curt, rude, and also showed signs of a person who deals with sort of thing often. I told him that I was upset that I had been forced to miss my appointment that I had showed up on time for, because of an error in their billing.  I then told him that this office seems to care more about getting paid than their patients.  To that, he stated that they are just "trying to stay afloat". (I couldn't believe he said that, we are talking medicine here, and everyone knows that Doctors, especially Specialty Doctors are not usually struggling.) I told him I would pay what the insurance stated that I owed, and that I want nothing else to do with this office. 
I would avoid this place at all costs. There are several bad reviews online, and I completely agree with them. In my opinion, this office does not care about their patients, just the amount of revenue they can generate. Patient be weary, this place is a rip off. The employees are very rude, condescending, and unhelpful.  Make sure that your bill from them backs up to what your insurance says you owe, because it is clear that they are ripping people off, are intolerant of anyone asking any questions regarding mistakes in billing (which happen more often than not), and are not there for your care or health. They exemplify everything that is wrong with healthcare, and are in the business of making money at all costs.
Great, caring staff. Charlie has a genuine interest in your well being. Bissell Chiro is the only chiro we use & recommend.

YUM!  Best pork chop of my life. . . .also the bloody mary's are really spicy and delicious.  My mouth is watering because I would love to have them both right now.  Service was good and atmosphere was great. 

Most everything we ordered was above and beyond what we had expected.

Frankford Hall is my to-go-to place for a large group of friends to drink, eat, and to talk without screaming at each other.  They got some imported German beers on draft.  It's not a crazy selection like you'd see at other German pubs/restaurants, but hey, you'd get served in a crazy large mug.  This place also got other game activities, like Jenga and ping-pong.  Awesome atmosphere for the spring/summer days.  

If it's your first time here, just grab a table on your own!  No waitress or waiters.  You just order on your own at a stand with a large menu banner outside!  You order and pay up front, then they'll hand you a stand with a number to be put at your table.  Someone will bring your food out.  Service is pretty fast here.  

The food itself is decent!  It's more Americanized German, but it's still good!  I'd recommend the Kaseschwein, or if you don't like sausage, get the Kanzler.   The Kartoffelpuffer were alright.  But their curry ketchup (in all dispenser btw.) is banging.  The Reisenpretezel is even better, but get it with the cheese dip.  It's hugggeeeeee and soft.

A great BYO option in Fairmount. I particularly like the deck on the top floor for outdoor dining. The food is consistently well prepared and a rotating list of specials add variety to the mix. They also have take-out service, which I've taken advantage of more times than I want to admit.

We found this place through yelp and so glad we did.  Bree was our server and she was fantastic!  We had the grilled grouper, the conch fritters, and the fried trio.  It was all delicious.  The atmosphere is casual and not too noisy.   I hear the key lime pie is delicious but I skipped it...we'll be back to get that on another trip.

Absolutely wonderful!  Messina (sp?) was very accommodating.  Justin was our server, and he provided exemplary customer service.  The food was outstanding, and the drinks were perfect.  If you have not been, you must go!  Thank you for helping make this the most amazing birthday!  We will definitely visit again.

Not a bad spot for "cafeteria" style food.  It's a supermarket/ restaurant.  One side is the supermarket, and the other side is the restaurant.  The market has pretty much everything that you would find in a typical Asian market.  As far as the restaurant goes, the people were pretty friendly and the prices weren't bad. We tried it for the first time when they had their bbq thing going on.  The squid we had was stuffed.  It wasn't bad, but my squid was cold.  My favorite thing here was the bbq chicken wings.  I liked the seasoning it had to it.  The pork bbq wasn't bad, either.  It was just done when we got it so it was still nice and hot.  I also got to try the Ube ice cream.  It was my first time having ube and it wasn't bad..  it tastes very creamy like it had coconut in it or something.

How do you screw up a franchise? The business model, the product, it's all laid out for you. Answer: hire the laziest, rudest, least enthusiastic women on the planet. Did you stop by the DMV and snatch these people up? Our orders were correct but they could not have rushed us any faster or been any nastier about our requests. Cut us off with "you done". Poor eye contact, laughing and screwing around taking our order in the background. You could walk into traffic and get hit by someone who would do a better job.

The owner takes great pride in all the food that he makes. There is a review on here talking about him smoking while making a pizza. Franco has never smoked in the shop. Also,you need two hands to make a pizza so it's  impossible to smoke while preparing one. If a pizza doesn't look right after it's baked, Franco won't even send it out!  Besides the pizza, the pasta platters are amazing and are restaurant quality. The portions are enough to feed two people so you can share.He also makes his own chicken tenders. They are really big,fresh and almost
look like whole chicken breasts and not at all like tenders. He makes his own mozzarella sticks too. You can tell because they're so big and fat,not like the frozen kind. Sandwiches are really tasty too! His homemade soups,especially the cream soups, are the best!
 I have never gotten anything from there that hasn't been delicious! If you're hungry, call Franco at Thin & Crispy for an amazing meal!

The Staybridge in Reno is by far one of the best places to stay. The small Kitchenete that was fully stocked not only helped keep our cost of food down but allowed us to continue eating and prepping healthy meals while away from home. The hotel cleanliness is impeccable and I love the fact that you don't have to smell smoke walking through a lobby area. The furniture, linens, and common facility areas where clean and kept in good repair. The room was big enough to feel comfortable and had the amenities to make it comfortable like home. By far the worst part of the stay for me is how the walls and doors don't insulated against sound. Every time someone entered or exited their room or the elevators and let the door close itself I woke up in the middle of the night along with people walking down the hallway talking.

My wife and I went to Marly's last night...We had goat cheese and chorizo croquettes as an appetizer which was very good. For entrees, we had the filet (marly's cheesesteak) and the haibut special. The filet was one of the best I've had anywhere. For desert, we had the banana chocolate layer cake which was excellent....Overall, I would say this is one of the best restaurants in Phoenixville and we only spent $87 for a great dinner.
Professional and Informative . Best products for your needs at the right price ! Great experience.  Quick install and considerate of customers time . Thanks Tint World!!!!

Came for our anniversary. All I can tell you is: Just so so people. Our Margheritta pizza was good: thin with a well baked crunchy crust, a smidgen of basil leaves and a few tomato slices; but it's not calling me back for more. My sangria was good, but nothing exceptional. My other half had a blood orange margarita. It was incredibly tart. We also had is simple salad. And yes it was quite simple. It was bagged leaf lettuce with four chunks of heirloom tomatoes along with a few tiny chunks of cucumber. On the menu, they say it comes with pistachio brittle. The brittle in the salad was teeny tiny slivers of sweet crunchy candies. On my pallet it didn't fit. I didn't taste any nuts so I picked them all out.

But it's the service that topped everything. The waitress was very polite. However she was absorbed with some sort of inventory device of some sort; and she along with another server were absorbed in a show on the TVs above the bar. It all resulted in me having to go up to retrieve her several times, first to order and then to get our toppings, and finally our check. She never asked if we wanted another drink or desert. I believe she never really heard me say we were there to celebrate our anniversary. 

Still the inside was really cozy and we enjoyed our time visiting. Again, another place experienced and another place I probably won't go back to.

UPDATE: the manager wrote me an apology and I spoke with the manager. So we will give them another go! Thanks!

I was glad that I had the opportunity to go to NOLA because like many I am a big fan of Emeril Lagasse.   The host and hostess were quite charming and made me feel welcomed.  The service was excellent and our waitress was quite helpful.  I had the garlic crusted drum fish, which was good but not outstanding.  I had enjoyed bread pudding at another restaurant earlier in the week and wanted to do a comparison.  Instead of being served in a more rustic style where the bread was visible and textured, this bread pudding had been disappointingly been put into a mold and was thus more like a gelatin--it was not to my taste both literally and figuratively. Was I totally disappointed in NOLA, not really.   But the proof of the pudding (pun intended) is would I go back to NOLA and the response is BAM! no I wouldn't.

I really can't imagine why anyone would give this a rating anything less than 4 stars. If you want to take a date on something "new and different" this is the perfect place. I have to be honest I was skeptical because of the new location because when I googled the place I didn't see any nice photos, but when my date and I arrived everything looked amazing! I told the owner she needs to post photos online of the new place because there weren't any.  Anyway, it was an awesome experience, when we arrived the tables were set up nicely, there was music playing, cheese plate, wine, really classy.  The owner was more than nice and really informative on different cooking techniques. We also met other nice couples which made the experience even better.  If you want to wow your date or simply want to do something different, look no further! Only thing I would say is location is a little hidden from the address posted on the site, it's really off of Hanson street. Only reason I say that is because it's not exactly in the best area to be aimlessly walking around. Other than that this is a Must Go!

TBH not very good :( everything I've tried had been less than satisfactory. Food takes too long, doesn't taste good and has a bad texture to it!? Tacos aren't that difficult. I'd say add some simple tacos. Don't need crispy chicken thigh just need GOOD TACOS UGH

I don't frequent many chain restaurants because there are so many wonderful local restaurants but I received a gift card from my coworkers (they are the best!) and treated my husband to dinner. This is a very nice Red Lobster with great service. I love their garlic cheddar biscuits and our server kept his eye on our basket and brought us some extra ones. It's these thoughtful touches that make the dining experience special! I had a combo plate and while everything was good the snow crab really stood out. Really good flavor and tasted fresh. If you're craving crab I really recommend this restaurant! The manager checked in with us while we were eating which is another great hallmark of thoughtful service. We will be adding this restaurant to our regular dining rotation!
The food was mediocre.  We couldn't tell the difference between the Lo Mein and the Pad Tai.  Sorry, but that's a one and done for us.

Love this local sushi house! Jillian is the best and the all you can eat lunch for $15.95 can't be beat. Includes all the saki too! After the burn we came here in a large group. They were so friendly and kept feeding us until we could all pop. Highly recommended.

One of my favorite dishes at any Thai restaurant is the drunken noodles. I love how the dish comes together so nicely to give you the perfect blend of spice and hear. Tap Thai's Drunken Noodles definitely does not disappoint. You get great flavor, fresh vegetables and a lingering and lasting heat that is in no way overwhelming.

Tap Thai also has what I think is the best Thai tea in town. I definitely would have given the venue 5 stars, however my one critique is that tho my dish tasted great. I requested a shrimp and chicken combo. They charged the 2.5 dollars for the added shrimp but only gave me 4 pieces of shrimp. In comparison to other Thai venues such as Pattaya, i feel like that's far less shrimp than I'm use to receiving. 

That said. I still highly recommend. The dish and the service was great.

It's great.  I would actually rate this place 4.5 stars.
We order the Tayim (salad, hummus, 2 apps, 1 entree and dessert).
The hummus/tahina is amazingly creamy and flavorful.  And when you eat it with the warm, homemade laffa - it's like you've gone to heaven.
The mezza (apps) standouts for me were the crispy haloumi (cheese) with date paste and fried kibbe.  I was a little disappointed with the kibbe naya.  It was not bad, but I have had better.  For the Shipudim (main entrees) all the meat dishes were very good - you won't go wrong with any of them.
We had 5 people in our group and there were 5 desserts, so we ordered one of each.  My fave was the cardamon- vanilla custard -- yummy!!  But any dessert you order, you will enjoy it.
If you like tapas styled food, this Middle Eastern fare will make you happy.

Food was amazing. Service is a bit lacking but that's because it is super super busy but the food is amazing! So tasty. If you are in New Orleans you must try out this place!!!! Trust me it's worth the wait!

Friendly service , unique offerings, fresh products. It's expensive no doubt, but it's a good place to go if you have what I call a "caviar craving " - for something luxe and decadent like a fat steak, fine cheese, or fancy chocolate.
Great smoothies and sandwiches. The Chicken Apple Club flat bread is very tasty. The app is a bit confusing and the staff weren't sure how to use it for rewards.

Hey! Finally this place wasn't a dark room. No complaints here service was good and food was good. Happy hour deal was on and i didnt have to remind the waitress either! 
Got nachos and wings and maaaaan! I was happy! The waitress was very vigilant and friendly. I will say i still find it wierd when kids are allowed into bars tho.

I had read some bad reviews. They are not to be believed. This place is amazing. Huge portions, good food, fast and friendly service. I have nothing bad to say. Our waitress (Christine I.) was an added bonus as well, both friendly and pleasant. The pull n' pop donuts are awesome. I can't wait to go back. Just not too soon as I am stuffed...

Review for body work services:

I've been piling up a few small insurance claims for a dent here, cracked bumper there, but when my leather steering wheel started to peel, it was the last straw. NOW it was time to get the car back in shape. I have a Subaru STi, which is considered by some their pet project or child, but I am not a car girl. The peer pressure has at least forced me to keep my bright blue wagon in decent shape, whilst not diving head first into Crazed CarLand.

Getting the estimate was easy. I just walked in one afternoon and it was done by Brian in a quick fashion. Turn-around time for bumper repair, some scratch/dent repair and a new steering wheel was about 5 days. The rates for labor were on par with the other estimate I received. I cannot say the same for Subaru and their priced-as-gold-plated parts.

I wasn't able to drop it off after hours, but made it work during the day. They did require me to put a parts deposit down when dropping it off.  The estimator called when their original repair plan wasn't working out and it was going to cost me a little more. I appreciated the communication more than my wallet appreciated the added cost, which wasn't really their fault. It also added some days. In the end, the time frame was at the very far end of what they estimated (4 full business days after the original 5).

Picking up the car: it was ready right at the time they said it would be and it was, to my surprise, clean. I was recently burned by a detail downtown and haven't had it done since. I would venture to say it was probably cleaner than that $150 detail I had previously, which was about a $25-worth service.

Body work is always worry some. Unless they're props, this place always has beautiful cars parked outside and in the shop, which can be reassuring (and make you feel like you ain't as cool as you think you are). I'd definitely recommend them for these kinds of things.
prices are wayyyy to high. food is mediocre for the price. save your money, go somewhere else

My mother brought me here for my birthday and I was not sure what to expect. I kind of expected it to be a typical soup and salad place where you stand in line feeling like you are at the cafeteria. It was kind of like that and it was a happier version of this. 
The lines move as fast as they do at Jimmy Johns. There is a huge menu. So, you forget what you want to order by the time you are placing an order and you forget what you ordered by the time you got to the register. The reason for this is because you order a ton of food and you get a ton of food!
I really liked this place and I hope to come back. I died and went to heaven when I had the turkey and avocado sandwich. I got a chicken and bacon salad with a vinaigrette and it was delicious! You get huge portions of just about everything. When you get a salad you get a huge chocolate covered strawberry. Be very careful with what you order because you get a strawberry with a soup and salad. You order both and you get more food than you bargained for. They also give you bread rolls. 
The beverages are awesome. They have the typical selection of soda, but when you look at the tea you will not be able to make up your mind! I saw a cucumber, basil green tea, but I chose some pomegranate tea and it was the best choice I ever made. If I go back I hope to try the other one. 
For desert I tried the cheese cake. It was absolute heaven! 
I am definitely coming back. I think this would be a cool place to hang out with my friends and family for lunch.

This is the worst service department I've ever experienced! If I could give them 0 stars I would. This service department has no integrity. 
I took my truck in for an issue with my headlights (not bulbs). I was told on Saturday that they had to order parts. Tuesday the service writer called me to tell me the parts are in and wanting to know when I can come in. I told him I was out of town and wouldn't be able to bring it in until Thursday morning. I arrived when they opened on Thursday and was told there was no appointment scheduled for me nor could the service writer that I had to deal with find a work order from the work they did on Saturday. I told her what they found and that the parts came in on Tuesday. She asked what lighting model was it? I told I didn't know. 
When I called to check on it in the afternoon they tell me that the parts just came in. Another lie. I came back to pick up my truck 30 minutes before they closed and I find out it's not ready. I ask what's going on with it and they finally tell me that it hasn't been looked at. Don't trust this dealership... lies are all they know!!!!

Called in for a sandwich and was greeted with someone who sounded like she was home as opposed to work. Ordered the 'Italian Sandwich.' Once home, I bit into it and immediately knew something was wrong. I lifted the bread to find this disaster. 
Some sort of old mystery meat. Luckily, I hadn't swallowed it. Didn't have time to return it but that's fine. I never want to see the place again. 

On the plus side, it was on a Sunday before football and the place was empty. Hopefully, it'll be gone soon. 

Hey, Earl. You suck!

Some absolutely amazing breakfast burritos right here. After a workout and Menlo Park (remember to exercise outdoors and stay safe!) this is an awesome place to eat outside so you can also maintain distance!

Recently I went to one of the big events called the chili bowl game 
My first impression of this field was I was shocked at how well it was kept up in comparison to similar fields in the local area
The game was a blast and the refs made sure that you have fun
I definitely will be returning to play for open play at this field

Seriously.  This place is directly across from my office and it's TERRIBLE.  I'm eating the General Tso's chicken right now and it's soggy.  I also have an order of the worst steamed pork dumplings I've ever had EVER.  The dumpling dough is so thick - it's thicker than peirogi dough.  Ick.  I'm contemplating opening my window and tossing these bad boys at the restaurant from my office window.  SHAME ON YOU, WOK! 

Do yourself a favor and WOK down Walnut St. to New Heaven on Walnut b/t 12th and 11th.  It's unendingly better.

These people are THIEVES! I moved from Miami to Harbour Island and toured the facility with a representative named, Sue. I mentioned that everything looked quite outdated and old, she PROMISED they were starting a massive remodel that very next week in the Mens Locker Room with brand new steam rooms and saunas. Reluctantly, I signed on. On my first visit, the group fitness studio had no air conditioning and the mens locker room was filled with bandaids in the lockers, hair balls and cracked tiles in the steam room, moldy shower curtains and dust filled air vents.

I emailed Sue and requested my membership cancellation considering the club was not how she described nor were the renovations actually underway (or actually happening). They charged me 3 months minimum to cancel my membership and then charged me a 4th. month on top of that! I drove the club to speak with the General Manager, Scott who refused to see me because he was "in a meeting" even though I said I would wait. Sue was no help and literally put me on the phone in her office with a corporate representative and she walked out. I have now been charged over $700 for stepping foot in that place TWICE!

They are liars, deceivers, thieves and manage a glorified YMCA. The club's conditions are horrible, it's dirty, unkept and outdated. STAY AWAY - You are way better off hiring a personal trainer to come to your house for the amount of money they will scam you from and the condescending treatment they will give you.

Conveniently located at the base of the Lupo building.  I ran in here yesterday to FedEx a package overnight.  The woman helping me (owner) was very nice and helpful.  They have the usual shipping stuff but I also noticed cards for the last minute kinds of peeps.
The is was outstanding. I had the duck, and my date had tuna. I must say the tuna was great and I don't eat fish. Great waiters and atmosphere.

The most amazing sandwich I ever had in my entire life! I was starving after getting my car fixed at VictoryAutoMall and said "why not check this place out". The first thing I noticed when I walked in was the size of the empanadas and how welcoming Oni and Marcos were. They gave me a brief history on authentic Cuban sandwiches. I learned that they get their bread from a bakery that is over 100 years old based out of Ybor City. I had the Mojito Pork sandwich and almost cried tears of joy and enjoyment. I will never eat another sandwich ever again, unless it's from Box of Cubans! #BoxofCubans
#TheLastSandwichYouwillEVERNEED
#Marco&OniGotThatGoodCubanStuff
#NothingButBoxofCubans
#BoC

Dr. Biscardi is a great! I haves lived in several places and always fear finding a new optometrist, so the Yelp reviews were important. She met all the expectations set. She and her staff are friendly, helpful, and attentive. She found my old prescription was over correcting my astigmatism. The new prescription is already much more comfortable. She also provided far more information on my eye conditions than any previous optometrist, which I really appreciate.

I went to the Minute Clinic at this location yesterday and had a very pleasant experience! I was a walk in and when I checked in I was told it would be a 23 min wait which was fine since I hadn't scheduled my appointment, but not even 2 mins after checking in I was seen. I wish I remembered my dr's name, because she was awesome. She was so kind and friendly, honestly one of my best experiences with a doctor. She made sure to check all of my medications after I informed her of my medical history and didn't rush me at all. We even had a really nice conversation about work clothes and she gave me some great advice on where to find comfy pants! My own doctor usually rushes me in and out of my appointments after making me wait 45 mins so this was a really nice change of pace. Once my appointment was done, my prescription was ready in 5 mins. They took my insurance (BCBS Arizona) and I had zero problems with my prescription or getting seen. Great service!

I wish I could do negative stars. Waitress put my debit card in her bra after taking her mask off while getting our order. Next time we come we went we were in line and bouncers were homophobic and did not let in our gay friend so we all left......
The fence looks great! Everyone was working hard, would definitely refer my friends to use you guys. Thank you

I'm a new tenant who just moved in about a month ago from California. I took a chance and gave a deposit before I even looked at the apartment in person, but I'm glad I did! April, the property manager, was very easy to work with and arranged for me to have my keys the Sunday night I arrived so that I wouldn't have to pay for a hotel stay :) 


Positives: 
1. The night I moved in, my freshly renovated apartment was SPOTLESS and move-in ready. I didn't have to clean ANYTHING and I'm someone who has allergies and is OCD about cleanliness. 
2. The kitchen is spacious with granite countertops, a large sink, and a decent amount of storage space. Apartment comes with your own washer/dryer too. 
3. It's safe- there is 24 hour security. Although, sometimes I do notice that the guards are away and leave the gate open but that's probably because they're attending to complaints or issues on the property. 
4. The gym is not bad and the pool area and property are well maintained. 
5. The neighbors I've met so far are very friendly. I never hear any loud music, etc. 
6. It's a very convenient location with Whole Foods, The Ochsner Medical Center, Barnes and Noble all being within a few mile radius. 
7. When I spoke to my other friends/classmates, I noticed that they paid significantly more for similar upgrades but smaller square footage. So, I'm satisfied with the rent I'm paying. 
8. The staff is very friendly and they take care of repairs and requests you make pretty fast. I accidentally dropped one of my diamond earrings in the sink and I immediately emailed April in the night to ask if someone could help me unscrew the sink pipe so I could get my earring out. Early next morning, the repairmen came over and retrieved my earring!


Negatives: 
1. I really enjoy studying and waking up to natural light, but with all the window curtains open there isn't much natural light coming into the apartment (this is a minor negative though). 
2.  I'm a an EXTREMELY light sleeper so in my bedroom I can hear cars passing by  but it's not very loud, doesn't keep me awake at night and it's something I'm getting used to. When I'm really tired, I hardly notice the noise outside.
3. I do find that the walls are thin and although I don't hear my neighbors talking, etc., I can definitely hear the shower, faucets and washing machines running. I guess the walls and pipes aren't very insulated. Again- this is a minor negative. 

Overall, the positives outweigh the negatives, so I'm overall very happy with my decision to live here and would highly recommend!

What a wonderful addition to the restaurant scene! The crab cakes, steak salad, fried green tomatoes, seafood salad, fries, oysters, steamed crab legs and drinks were fantastic!  It really reminded me of a MD style restaurant that we've needed in Phila for a long time!  Wonderful night out with the girls celebrating birthdays and the piano bar made it even more entertaining!  I highly recommend and we will back for the amazing food, service, hospitality and fun atmosphere! Thank you to the staff for making our night so memorable!

I live on the same block at this Doggie Style so it is incredibly convenient. My dog gets groomed here every couple of months and they always do a great job.  He is incredibly nervous and anxious but they are very patient with him. Also, there is one sales attendant, a gentleman with a beard, who is so helpful with suggestions and seems really knowledgeable. He helped me a pick a good easily digestible food when my dog was having trouble.

The food was on the salty side. Waitress never came back to check on how we were doing and if we needed anything. I ate my hamburger because I was starving and had to feed my 22 month old. My mother in law had to put lots of ketchup on her burger to take the saltyness away. My wives flatbread was not good at all. We told the waitress at the end, of course there was no response. She had the manager come over and asked us how everything was. I explained to him about how salty the food was and how my wives food wasn't very good. Plus I mentioned to him the waitress never came back to see how we were doing. His answer was, "ummmmm not sure why this happened". That was our answer. Never came back. We got the bill and paid it. Left the restaurant sick to our stomach because of the way they treated us

Tiny hole in the wall bar. Always gotta love a good dive!

We took the recommendation of Alligator and Swiss poboy and tacked on Red Beans and Rice on top of it. Man, was it good! Definitely will visit next time in town!

There are so many levels of incompetence in this company it is ridiculous.  From techs not showing to the inability to control an issue, this company is horrible.  Stay as far away as possible from this company.

I saw their stand at the Capital City Market and the cookies looked really good and were 3 for $5.  I knew I would be in Eagle in an hour so decided to visit their shop instead thinking they would be a bit more fresh.  The shop is cute and nice inside.  The lady at the counter was friendly.  I asked how the frosting the was made and she said "Crisco".  I'll pass on the partially hydrogenated trans fat.  When I mentioned it there was a bit of an attitude.  She said they needed it to make it fluffy and I simply informed her there were brands that didn't have trans fats, albeit more expensive.  She said she would talk to the owner, which was nice.  I mentioned I was at the City Market earlier and they had the price at 3 for $5.  She said they do not honor that price in the store and I would have to pay $2/cookie.  I tried to reason with her that I was making a special stop to visit the actual store location and she simply did not care one bit.  I ordered a snickerdoodle, brookie, ginger, and chocolate crinkle.  I tried again when I paid to get the 3 for $5 deal and was turned down.  I told her I would call the owner to mention this is poor customer service and she said "why don't you go ahead and do that".  Very rude when I did not have an attitude about it one bit, just trying to get it through that it was a ridiculous policy.  Anyway....to the cookies.  They are horrible!!  So very dry and even though they were all different cookies, they somehow seemed to taste the same.  I think they must use the same base???!!  The chocolate was poor quality and snickerdoodles usually have a nice cream of tartar flavor and this had none.  It was so dry my mouth needed some water afterwards.  I just don't see how these guys stay in business with their awful cookies and poor customer service.  I wish Nancy's Cookies was still around, they knew how to do it and each of their cookies had a distinct flavor.  Never, ever will I give them my business again.  I actually joined Yelp just so I could write this review and express how bad this place is.  Hope people listen...

I wanted to get a Covid test prior to visiting family, so scheduled an appointment for the drive-through testing. I picked this location because it's one of the Louisiana Department of Health "no cost" locations. Note that it's important to verify that prior to making your appointment. You'll be requested to enter your insurance details if you have it, but won't be charged if your insurance declines to pay. I wasn't able to schedule an appointment for same day testing, but could schedule the following day. An email confirmation was sent a few hours later informing me of my appointment instructions. On the day of my appointment, I arrived 7 minutes early and they were ready for me. They walked me through administering my own test and I was done within a minute. I was nervous about how long the results would take, but it only took 1.5 days to get my results online. I highly recommend this Walgreens for anyone needing a quick and convenient Covid test.

This place was fantastic. Anita was as nice and helpful as could be. And she had everything you need, even a fine selection of hops -- which really says a lot these days, given that there's a major hop-shortage going on. 

Listen, I guess there's a homebrew place in San Diego that has an adjoining tasting room and actually lets you try the different grains. I don't know if that would be permitted here. But even so, in an industry with so little competition, where Anita would do just fine to rest on her laurels, Great Fermentations continues to meet great expectations. Start a new hobby or just drop in to browse. But don't miss this jewel of a local business.

It should be noted that Great Fermentations is just as good for the homebrewing of WINE as beer. Enthusiasts of either hobby are luck to have it.

I love this location on the river sitting outside and the place inside too
It's always pretty good  as far as food and service go and a fun atmosphere. High energy and unique in terms of the d.j. That may or may not regularly be there but he was while we were and it was quite a spectacle. 
Also, Hands down Best crab in town.

Oh those hot delicious shoestring fries!!!!!!!!!

And The Freddy sauce is addictive.

Delicious hand made steak burger--not your run of the mill burger.

All their offerings looked super!
All I ask is for common courtesy..."thank you" or "you're welcome" by the lady taking my money.

This was my first stop in Nashville and the food was amazing. If you're looking for some soul food with that home cooking feel, this is the place for you. The only thing I regret is not ordering more food.

Absolutely wonderful. Nothing but 100% AMAZING things to say about Cadiz! Max & Ricardo are absolutely PERFECT and example the upmost professionalism and etiquette. I personally run a marketing/advertising company focusing on hospitality and restaurant industry's and would recommend this restaurant to all of my subscribers and wouldn't doubt a single thing! IF YOU COME TO SANTA BARBARA YOU HAVE TO COME HERE!

It's a basic gym. If you're looking for a gym and would like a convenient place thats rarely crowded, this is a decent option. 

They offer a good array of classes, and usually you're able to get into them. There are a few racketball courts (if you're into that) and a mixed use room that is open while classes are not in session. 

The treadmills, ellipticals, rowing machine, and stair steppers are old. These could use some updating. Additionally, the assisted LifeCycle machines are dated. 

For a gym this size, I would expect them to have more of a variety of machines. 

Overall, this is a good gym to start with.
Very friendly and helpful staff. Easy returns online or in the store. Good quality clothes.

I am extremely satisfied with all of my services I got  today! So much that I wanted to make sure I put this review because I was so grateful and happy. To start off I walked in without having an appointment the woman at the front asked me to wash my hands before getting started which is nice knowing everyone coming in starts off by washing their hands. I told the woman I wanted a pedi and a fill in for my nails. As soon as I got comfortable in the pedi chair a man immediately started setting up for the pedicure and brought out an ice cold water bottle. I'm pregnant and it was pretty hot outside so this was a nice treat. And surprisingly most places don't offer water. The man stared on my pedi, he handed me a menu with services and price list, I selected what I wanted and he began by giving me options for which pedicure scent I wanted. This was nice because iv never have the option. I picked mint 
Eucalyptus. Some of my toe nails were very short and uneven, so after the gentleman gave me a very nice relaxing pedi the women that first greeted me gave me an over lay to make them all match. She was extremely thorough and took her time. She also smoothed down my nails that I have previously had done from another shop because I told her they were bulkier then I typically like them and that if she couldn't fix it, it wouldn't be her fault. But she did!! My acrylics are perfectly shaped, not bumpy or thick. I had a total of 3 people work on my hands and feet and it didn't feel rushed at all. Anyways. I loved my experience today! Thanks so much!

Yuckity-yuck-YUCK!  

I don't know why these other reviewers drive so far for such measly fare, however there are much yummier restaurants in SB!!

I've been here twice - once for lunch & once for dinner.
The bread is tasty & is probably the best thing offered.

The lunch visit consisted of surly service, very average & somewhat odd piccata & a decent pizza.  

The dinner visit - painstakingly slow & impersonal service...  maybe our waiter didn't care, because the gratuity was already predetermined since we were a party of 6 or perhaps because he already knew he would be bringing out miserably mediocre food.

Two friends ordered pizzas and they looked good; I ordered an Italian classic - chicken parmigiana - and it tasted like oversalted, canned sauce on soggy breaded chicken.  I had the option of subbing out the accompanying fettuccine alfredo for "Italian broccoli" (because "at Pascucci, we believe in choices" read the menu... I wish they were bigger believers in good food).  Unfortunately, the bread crumbs with garlic on broccoli was really more of a broccoli stuffing concoction - I don't know if they know this, but broccoli can't bite.... you really don't have to cook the hell out of it until all shades of green have seeped away.

In any case, there are at least 50 other restaurants in this price range on State Street that will prove infinitely more satisfying!!!

What no option to add "Polish" or even "Eastern European" to the categories?  C'mon, yelp!

This is more of a bar with some booths.  Not to be confused with the New Wave Cafe in South Philly, this New Wave is in Port Richmond and serves authentic Polish food.  The small bar was filled with people speaking in Polish when we visited.  Everyone was drinking Polish beer.  We wanted to try what they had, but we couldn't pronounce it.  But the Okocim (nicknamed OK beer) was pronounceable and tasty.  The soup was great, but the golabki and pierogies were, in my opinion, just okay.  Then again, nothing tastes like my grandmother's golabki.

It took a lo-o-o-ng time to get our food after ordering.  But when I went to the ladies room, I passed the kitchen and saw one Polish lady hard at work.  With that in mind, New Wave is authentic, homemade Polish food.

What a cute and quaint little coffee/tea shop, with bistro type foods to eat! We stopped in here on whim to waste some time before attending a wedding... AND BOY WERE WE SURPRISED!!! They have the cutest rooms for you to be seated while you enjoy your order. They even have a creative room to help get the CREATIVE JUICES FOLLOWING! There is also a little area to shop for little items made my local artist. The items in the area range from handmade necklaces to scarfs to magnets and post cards. If you ever find yourself in the area... DO STOP IN!!

I was excited to checkout this Marriott property. Luckily I was only here for one night. The place is very outdated and the design of the rooms are horrible. The pool is inside the atrium. I was woken up by kids yelling in the pool and then at 8am, housekeeping was knocking on my door. Check out was at 12pm. 

This hotel needs better customer service. The staff didn't seem like they wanted to be helpful in explaining things. I had called around 10 am and requested a late checkout, which I can get for 4pm (Marriott elite benefit) The rude employee said she can do 12:30. What's the point of 30 minutes?

Hotel left a bad taste in my mouth and it certainly didn't help being in a very small room and being woken up early.
Love the pizzas and calzones. Always get great pizza and decent service. Holy Shiitake is amazing and red sangria is delicious.

What an unusual gallery space...I love it!

First of all, I've been wanting to check this place out for a while. It stands out from the rest of the galleries in the area. It's design, their signage, and they way they display things is very clean and professional, reminding me more of the galleries in Chicago and NYC rather than some of it's kitschy-er neighbors down the street. It was great to finally pay a visit while everything was in full swing for First Friday. 

[I'm not embarrassed to say that I absolutely tried to enter through the large, non-functioning wooden doors on the outside. They are gigantic, and the very notion that they could open made me very happy and feeling like Alice In Wonderland.]

The gallery interior is large as well. A show featuring downed trees from Hurricane Sandy in NYC was opening; walking into a large room with tons of abstracted, organic objects was pretty surreal. It seemed as though it would be right on cue that a very enthusiastic gallery attendant greeted us and began telling all about the artist and his show. This lady was the fun fact queen! My friend and I made our way around the show and ended up in another room where the gallery attendant started chatting with us again. She was really knowledgable and excited to engage in conversations about the work, artists, and the gallery owner himself.  I enjoyed talking to her and hearing her stories. 

I will definitely be hitting up The Center for Art in Wood whenever I'm in Old City to see who's showing! The upstairs museum is also a must-see anytime, and forever. A true Philly gem!

LOVE THIS PLACE. Good service, delicious food, and a great atmosphere. What more can you ask for???
I would give it 5 stars but every pizza i have ordered somehow falls apart, the cheese falls off and the crust is so thin and does not hold shape at all. However it still is delicious!  We love the Proscuitto and burrata plate and order it with bread. It melts in your mouth and it is one of my favorite things ever.

I love Saturday morning Jivamukti. Beth is a great teacher and the classes are very welcoming and accessible. I'm not in shape and had never done yoga before but the group made me feel right at ease. I love how I feel after class.

This place doesn't look like much from the outside but once you get your food you'll be in heaven. The Red Dragon Roll is amazing. The seaweed salad and crashing are also great. They pay great attention to detail, presentation and taste. No need to go anywhere else!!!
Pizza is a sold 4 star. Very impressed with the red sauce . Wings are good but the mild ones need more flavor and they need to give more blue cheese

Excellent food and drinks!  Checked in via yelp and confirmed upon arrival. After waiting over 20 min we went back to the hostess desk to inquire and they had forgotten our party of 6. Ended up late for bowl game. Everyone enjoyed their meal tho!

The Sichuan style cuisine here is very delicious,I had gone to many chinese restaurants in Philadelphia, I think I can say this cuisine is authentic like what I eat in China. I like grilled fish，after finish the fish I was suggested to take the soup back to my home. Today I use this soup to do hot pot，It still has good taste.
Didn't want to leave 1 star Too freakin slow in the drive thru.... 35 minute wait for $10 worth of food.
